obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line 1
  line `THE INCOME-TAX ACT, 1961`
  line ____________
  line `ARRANGEMENT OF SECTIONS`
  line ____________
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `1. Short title, extent and commencement.`
  line `2. Definitions.`
  line `3. “Previous year” defined.`
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `B ASIS OF CHARGE`
  line `4. Charge of income-tax.`
  line `5. Scope of total income.`
  line `5A. Apportionment of income between spouses governed by Portuguese Civil Code.`
  line `6. Residence in India.`
  line `7. Income deemed to be received.`
  line `8. Dividend income.`
  line `9. Income deemed to accrue or arise in India.`
  line `9A. Certain activities not to constitute business connection in India.`
  line `CHAPTER III`
  line `I NCOMES WHICH DO NOT FORM PART OF TOTAL INCOME`
  line `10. Incomes not included in total income.`
  line `10A. Special provision in respect of newly established undertakings in free trade zone, etc.`
  line `10AA. Special provisions in respect of newly established Units in Special Economic Zones.`
  line `10B. Special provisions in respect of newly established hundred per cent. export-oriented undertakings.`
  line `10BA. Special provisions in respect of export of certain articles or things.`
  line `10BB. Meaning of computer programmes in certain cases.`
  line `10C. Special provision in respect of certain industrial undertakings in North-Eastern Region.`
  line `11. Income from property held for charitable or religious purposes.`
  line `12. Income of trusts or institutions from contributions.`
  line `12A. Conditions for applicability of sections 11 and 12.`
  line `12AA. Procedure for registration.`
  line `13. Section 11 not to apply in certain cases.`
  line `13A. Special provision relating to incomes of political parties.`
  line `13B. Special provisions relating to voluntary contributions received by electoral trust.`
  line ` Subject to verification and confirmation by the Department.`
