obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line 30
  line `THE INCOME-TAX ACT, 1961`
  line `A CT N O. 43 OF 1961`
  line `[13 th September, 1961.]`
  line `An Act to consolidate and amend the law relating to income-tax and super-tax.`
  line `B E it enacted by Parliament in the Twelfth Year of the Republic of India as follows: —`
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `1. Short title, extent and commencement. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called the Income-tax Act, 1961.`
  line `( 2 ) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line `( 3 ) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, it shall come into force on the 1st day of April, 1962.`
  line `2. Definitions. — In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `1 [( 1 ) “ advance tax ” means the advance tax payable in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `Chapter XVII-C;]`
  line `2 [( 1A )] “ agricultural income ” means —`
  line `3 [( a ) any rent or revenue derived from land which is situated in India and is used for`
  line `agricultural purposes;]`
  line `( b ) any income derived from such land by —`
  line `( i ) agriculture; or`
  line `( ii ) the performance by a cultivator or receiver of rent-in-kind of any process ordinarily`
  line `employed by a cultivator or receiver of rent-in-kind to render the produce raised or received`
  line `by him fit to be taken to market; or`
  line `( iii ) the sale by a cultivator or receiver of rent-in-kind of the produce raised or received`
  line `by him, in respect of which no process has been performed other than a process of the nature`
  line `described in paragraph ( ii ) of this sub-clause;`
  line `( c ) any income derived from any building owned and occupied by the receiver of the rent or`
  line `revenue of any such land, or occupied by the cultivator or the receiver of rent-in-kind, of any land`
  line `with respect to which, or the produce of which, any process mentioned in paragraphs ( ii ) and ( iii )`
  line `of sub-clause ( b ) is carried on:`
  line `4 [Provided that —`
  line `( i ) the building is on or in the immediate vicinity of the land, and is a building which the`
  line `receiver of the rent or revenue or the cultivator, or the receiver of rent-in-kind, by reason of`
  line `his connection with the land, requires as a dwelling house, or as a store-house, or other out-`
  line `building, and`
  line `( ii ) the land is either assessed to land revenue in India or is subject to a local rate assessed`
  line `and collected by officers of the Government as such or where the land is not so assessed to`
  line `land revenue or subject to a local rate, it is not situated —`
  line ` Subject to verification and confirmation by the Department.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Clause ( 1 ) renumbered as clause ( 1A ), ibid., s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 2, for sub-clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
