  line `( iii ) shareholders holding not less than 1 [three-fourths] in value of the shares in the`
  line `amalgamating company or companies (other than shares already held therein immediately before`
  line `the amalgamation by, or by a nominee for, the amalgamated company or its subsidiary) become`
  line `shareholders of the amalgamated company by virtue of the amalgamation,`
  line `otherwise than as a result of the acquisition of the property of one company by another company`
  line `pursuant to the purchase of such property by the other company or as a result of the distribution of`
  line `such property to the other company after the winding up of the first-mentioned company;]`
  line `2 [( 1C ) “ Additional Commissioner ” means a person appointed to be an Additional Commissioner`
  line `of Income-tax under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 117;`
  line `( 1D ) “ Additional Director ” means a person appointed to be an Additional Director of Income-tax`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 117;]`
  line `( 2 ) “ annual value ”, in relation to any property, means its annual value as determined`
  line `under section 23;`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `( 4 ) “ Appellate Tribunal ” means the Appellate Tribunal constituted under section 252;`
  line `( 5 ) “ approved gratuity fund ” means a gratuity fund which has been and continues to be approved`
  line `by the 4 [ 5 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 6 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner]] in accordance with the rules contained in Part C of the Fourth Schedule;`
  line `( 6 ) “ approved superannuation fund ” means a superannuation fund or any part of a superannuation`
  line `fund which has been and continues to be approved by the 4 [ 5 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner] or 6 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] in accordance with the rules`
  line `contained in Part B of the Fourth Schedule;`
  line `( 7 ) “assesse” means a person by whom 7 [any tax] or any other sum of money is payable under`
  line `this Act, and includes —`
  line `( a ) every person in respect of whom any proceeding under this Act has been taken for the`
  line `8 [assessment of his income or assessment of fringe benefits] or of the income of any other person`
  line `in respect of which he is assessable, or of the loss sustained by him or by such other person, or of`
  line `the amount of refund due to him or to such other person;`
  line `( b ) every person who is deemed to be an assessee under any provision of this Act;`
  line `( c ) every person who is deemed to be an assessee in default under any provision of this Act;`
  line `9 [( 7A ) “Assessing Officer” means the 10 [ 11 [Assistant Commissioner or Deputy Commissioner] or`
  line `12 [Assistant Director or Deputy Director]] or the Income-tax Officer who is vested with the relevant`
  line `jurisdiction by virtue of directions or orders issued under sub-section ( 1 ) orsub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 120 or any other provision of this Act, and the 2 [Additional Commissioner or]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 3, for “nine - tenth” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2000).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-6-1994).`
  line `3. Sub-section ( 3 ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 126 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 4, for “income - tax or super tax” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 3, for “assessment of his income” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `10. Sub s. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 3, for “Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1996).`
  line `1 1. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 3, for “Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `12. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for “Assistant Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
