  line 33
  line `1 [Additional Director or] 2 [Joint Commissioner or Joint Director] who is directed under clause ( b ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 4 ) of that section to exercise or perform all or any of the powers and functions conferred`
  line `on, or assigned to, an Assessing Officer under this Act;]`
  line `( 8 ) “ assessment ” includes reassessment;`
  line `( 9 ) “ assessment year ” means the period of twelve months commencing on the 1st day of April`
  line `every year;`
  line `3 [( 9A ) “ Assistant Commissioner ” means a person appointed to be an Assistant Commissioner of`
  line `Income-tax 4 [or a Deputy Commissioner of Income-tax] under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 117;]`
  line `5 [( 9B ) “ Assistant Director ” means a person appointed to be an Assistant Director of Income-tax`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 117;]`
  line `( 10 ) “ average rate of income-tax ” means the rate arrived at by dividing the amount of income-tax`
  line `calculated on the total income, by such total income;`
  line `6 [( 11 ) “ block of assets ” means a group of assets falling within a class of assets comprising —`
  line `( a ) tangible assets, being buildings, machinery, plant or furniture;`
  line `( b ) intangible assets, being know-how, patents, copyrights, trade-marks, licences, franchises`
  line `or any other business or commercial rights of similar nature,`
  line `in respect of which the same percentage of depreciation is prescribed;]`
  line `( 12 ) “ Board ” means the 7 [Central Board of Direct Taxes constituted under the Central Boards of`
  line `Revenue Act, 1963 (54 of 1963)];`
  line `8 [( 12A ) “ books or books of account ” includes ledgers, day-books, cash books, account-books and`
  line `other books, whether kept in the written form or as print-outs of data stored in a floppy, disc, tape or`
  line `any other form of electro-magnetic data storage device;]`
  line `( 13 ) “ business ” includes any trade, commerce or manufacture or any adventure or concern in the`
  line `nature of trade, commerce or manufacture;`
  line `9 [( 13A ) “ business trust ” means a trust registered as, —`
  line `( i ) an Infrastructure Investment Trust under the Securities and Exchange Board of India`
  line `(Infrastructure Investment Trusts) Regulations, 2014 made under the Securities and Exchange`
  line `Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992); or`
  line `( ii ) a Real Estate Investment Trust under the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Real`
  line `Estate Investment Trusts) Regulations, 2014 made under the Securities and Exchange Board of`
  line `India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992), and`
  line `the units of which are required to be listed on recognised stock exchange in accordance with the`
  line `aforesaid regulations;]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-10-1996).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 4, for “Deputy Commissioner or Deputy Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 4, for clause ( 11 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 54 of 1963, s. 5, for “Central Board of Revenue constituted under the Central Board of Revenue`
  line `Act, 1924 (4 of 1924)” ( w.e.f. 1-1-1964).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-6-2001).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 3, for clause ( 13A ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
