  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  sourcePage 35
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line 35
  line `1 [( b ) in any area within the distance, measured aerially, —`
  line `( I ) not being more than two kilometres, from the local limits of any municipality or`
  line `cantonment board referred to in item (a) and which has a population of more than ten`
  line `thousand but not exceeding one lakh; or`
  line `( II ) not being more than six kilometres, from the local limits of any municipality or`
  line `cantonment board referred to in item (a) and which has a population of more than one`
  line `lakh but not exceeding ten lakh; or`
  line `( III ) not being more than eight kilometres, from the local limits of any municipality`
  line `or cantonment board referred to in item (a) and which has a population of more than ten`
  line lakh.
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-clause, “ population ” means the population`
  line `according to the last preceding census of which the relevant figures have been published before`
  line `the first day of the previous year;]]`
  line `2 [( iv ) 6½ per cent.. Gold Bonds, 1977, 3 [or 7 per cent.. Gold Bonds, 1980], 4 [or National Defence`
  line `Gold Bonds, 1980], issued by the Central Government;]`
  line `5 [( v ) Special Bearer Bonds, 1991, issued by the Central Government;]`
  line `6 [( vi ) Gold Deposit Bonds issued under the Gold Deposit Scheme, 1999 7 [or deposit certificates`
  line `issued under the Gold Monetisation Scheme, 2015] notified by the Central Government.]`
  line `8 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that “ property ” includes and`
  line `shall be deemed to have always included any rights in or in relation to an Indian company,`
  line `including rights of management or control or any other rights whatsoever;]`
  line `9 [( 15 ) “ charitable purpose ” includes relief of the poor, education, 10 [yoga,] medical relief,`
  line `11 [preservation of environment (including watersheds, forests and wildlife) and preservation of`
  line `monuments or places or objects of artistic or historic interest,] and the advancement of any other`
  line `object of general public utility:`
  line `12 [Provided that the advancement of any other object of general public utility shall not be a`
  line `charitable purpose, if it involves the carrying on of any activity in the nature of trade, commerce or`
  line `business, or any activity of rendering any service in relation to any trade, commerce or business, for a`
  line `cess or fee or any other consideration, irrespective of the nature of use or application, or retention, of`
  line `the income from such activity, unless —`
  line `( i ) such activity is undertaken in the course of actual carrying out of such advancement of`
  line `any other object of general public utility; and`
  line `( ii ) the aggregate receipts from such activity or activities during the previous year, do not`
  line `exceed twenty per cent. of the total receipts, of the trust or institution undertaking such activity or`
  line `activities, of that previous year;]]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 3, for item (b) (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 54 of 1962, s. 2 (w.e.f.13-12-1962).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 15 of 1965, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 41 of 1965, s. 2 (w.e.f. 4-12-1965).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 7 of 1981, s. 5 (w.e.f. 12-1-1981).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016)`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 3, for clause (15) (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `11. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
  line `12. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 3, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
