obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line 37
  line `1 [( ac ) if it is a mutual benefit finance company, that is to say, a company which carries on, as`
  line `its principal business, the business of acceptance of deposits from its members and which is`
  line `declared by the Central Government under section 620A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956),`
  line `to be a Nidhi or Mutual Benefit Society; or]`
  line `2 [( ad ) if it is a company, wherein shares (not being shares entitled to a fixed rate of dividend`
  line `whether with or without a further right to participate in profits) carrying not less than fifty per`
  line `cent.. of the voting power have been allotted unconditionally to, or acquired unconditionally by,`
  line `and were throughout the relevant previous year beneficially held by, one or more co-operative`
  line societies;]
  line `3 [( b ) if it is a company which is not a private company as defined in the Companies Act,`
  line `1956 (1 of 1956), and the conditions specified either in item ( A ) or in item ( B ) are fulfilled,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( A ) shares in the company (not being shares entitled to a fixed rate of dividend whether`
  line `with or without a further right to participate in profits) were, as on the last day of the relevant`
  line `previous year, listed in a recognised stock exchange in India in accordance with the Securities`
  line `Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956), and any rules made thereunder;`
  line `4 [( B ) shares in the company (not being shares entitled to a fixed rate of dividend whether`
  line `with or without a further right to participate in profits) carrying not less than fifty per cent.. of`
  line `the voting power have been allotted unconditionally to, or acquired unconditionally by, and`
  line `were throughout the relevant previous year beneficially held by —`
  line `( a ) the Government, or`
  line `( b ) a corporation established by a Central, State or Provincial Act, or`
  line `( c ) any company to which this clause applies or any subsidiary company of such`
  line `company 5 [if the whole of the share capital of such subsidiary company has been held by`
  line `the parent company or by its nominees throughout the previous year].`
  line `Explanation. — In its application to an Indian company whose business consists mainly in the`
  line `construction of ships or in the manufacture or processing of goods or in mining or in the generation or`
  line `distribution of electricity or any other form of power, item ( B ) shall have effect as if for the words`
  line `“ not less than fifty per cent. ”, the words “ not less than forty per cent. ” had been substituted;]]`
  line `( 19 ) “ co-operative society ” means a co-operative society registered under the Co-operative`
  line `Societies Act, 1912 (2 of 1912), or under any other law for the time being in force in any State for the`
  line `registration of co-operative societies;`
  line `6 [( 19A ) “ Deputy Commissioner ” means a person appointed to be a Deputy Commissioner of`
  line `Income-tax 7 *** under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 117;`
  line `8 [( 19AA ) “ demerger ”, in relation to companies, means the transfer, pursuant to a scheme of`
  line `arrangement under sections 391 to 394 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), by a demerged`
  line `company of its one or more undertakings to any resulting company in such a manner that —`
  line `( i ) all the property of the undertaking, being transferred by the demerged company,`
  line `immediately before the demerger, becomes the property of the resulting company by virtue of the`
  line demerger;
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 1985, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1984).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 14 of 1969, s. 3, for sub-clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1970).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 11 of 1983, s. 3, for item ( B ) (w.e.f. 2-4-1983).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 74, for “where such subsidiary company fulfils the conditions laid down in clause ( b ) of`
  line `section 108” ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `7. The words “or an Additional Commissioner of Income - tax” omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
