obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line 39
  line `companies, as the case may be, shall be deemed to be a demerger if such split up or reconstruction`
  line `fulfils 1 [such conditions as may be notified in the Official Gazette, by the Central Government;]`
  line `2 [ Explanation 5. — For the purposes of this clause, the reconstruction or splitting up of a company,`
  line `which ceased to be a public sector company as a result of transfer of its shares by the Central`
  line `Government, into separate companies, shall be deemed to be a demerger, if such reconstruction or`
  line `splitting up has been made to give effect to any condition attached to the said transfer of shares and`
  line `also fulfils such other conditions as may be notified by the Central Government in the Official`
  line Gazette.]
  line `( 19AAA ) “ demerged company ” means the company whose undertaking is transferred, pursuant to`
  line `a demerger, to a resulting company;]`
  line `( 19B ) “ Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) ” means a person appointed to be a Deputy`
  line `Commissioner of Income-tax (Appeals) 3 [or an Additional Commissioner of Income-tax (Appeals)]`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 117;]`
  line `3 [( 19C ) “ Deputy Director ” means a person appointed to be a Deputy Director of Income-tax 4 ***`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 117;]`
  line `( 20 ) “ director ”, “ manager ” and “ managing agent ”, in relation to a company, have the meanings`
  line `respectively assigned to them in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line `5 [( 21 ) “ Director General or Director ” means a person appointed to be a Director General of`
  line `Income-tax or a Principal Director General of Income-tax or, as the case may be, a Director of`
  line `Income-tax or a Principal Director of Income-tax, under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 117, and includes a`
  line `person appointed under that sub-section to be an Additional Director of Income-tax or a Joint`
  line `Director of Income-tax or an Assistant Director or Deputy Director of Income-tax;]`
  line `( 22 ) “ dividend ” includes —`
  line `( a ) any distribution by a company of accumulated profits, whether capitalised or not, if such`
  line `distribution entails the release by the company to its shareholders of all or any part of the assets`
  line `of the company;`
  line `( b ) any distribution to its shareholders by a company of debentures, debenture-stock, or`
  line `deposit certificates in any form, whether with or without interest, and any distribution to its`
  line `preference shareholders of shares by way of bonus, to the extent to which the company possesses`
  line `accumulated profits, whether capitalised or not;`
  line `( c ) any distribution made to the shareholders of a company on its liquidation, to the extent to`
  line `which the distribution is attributable to the accumulated profits of the company immediately`
  line `before its liquidation, whether capitalised or not;`
  line `( d ) any distribution to its shareholders by a company on the reduction of its capital, to the`
  line `extent to which the company possesses accumulated profits which arose after the end of the`
  line `previous year ending next before the 1st day of April, 1933, whether such accumulated profits`
  line `have been capitalised or not;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 3, for “the conditions specified in sub -clauses ( i ) to ( vii ) of this clause, to the extent`
  line `applicable” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2000).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 47 of 2016, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-6-1994).`
  line `4. The words “or an Additional Director of Income - tax” omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 3, for clause ( 21 ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
