  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  sourcePage 40
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line 40
  line `( e ) any payment by a company, not being a company in which the public are substantially`
  line `interested, of any sum (whether as representing a part of the assets of the company or otherwise)`
  line `1 [made after the 31st day of May, 1987, by way of advance or loan to a shareholder, being a`
  line `person who is the beneficial owner of shares (not being shares entitled to a fixed rate of dividend`
  line `whether with or without a right to participate in profits) holding not less than ten per cent. of the`
  line `voting power, or to any concern in which such shareholder is a member or a partner and in which`
  line `he has a substantial interest (hereafter in this clause referred to as the said concern)] or any`
  line `payment by any such company on behalf, or for the individual benefit, of any such shareholder, to`
  line `the extent to which the company in either case possesses accumulated profits;`
  line `but “ dividend ” does not include —`
  line `( i ) a distribution made in accordance with sub-clause ( c ) or sub-clause ( d ) in respect of any`
  line `share issued for full cash consideration, where the holder of the share is not entitled in the event`
  line `of liquidation to participate in the surplus assets;`
  line `2 [( ia ) a distribution made in accordance with sub-clause ( c ) or sub-clause ( d ) in so far as such`
  line `distribution is attributable to the capitalised profits of the company representing bonus shares`
  line `allotted to its equity shareholders after the 31st day of March, 1964 3 [and before the 1st day of`
  line `April, 1965];]`
  line `( ii ) any advance or loan made to a shareholder 4 [or the said concern] by a company in the`
  line `ordinary course of its business, where the lending of money is a substantial part of the business of`
  line `the company;`
  line `( iii ) any dividend paid by a company which is set off by the company against the whole or`
  line `any part of any sum previously paid by it and treated as a dividend within the meaning of sub-`
  line `clause ( e ), to the extent to which it is so set off;`
  line `5 [( iv ) any payment made by a company on purchase of its own shares from a shareholder in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of section 77A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line `( v ) any distribution of shares pursuant to a demerger by the resulting company to the`
  line `shareholders of the demerged company (whether or not there is a reduction of capital in the`
  line `demerged company).]`
  line `Explanation 1. — The expression “ accumulated profits ”, wherever it occurs in this clause, shall`
  line `not include capital gains arising before the 1st day of April, 1946, or after the 31st day of March,`
  line `1948, and before the 1st day of April, 1956.`
  line `Explanation 2. — The expression “ accumulated profits ” in sub-clauses ( a ), ( b ), ( d ) and ( e ), shall`
  line `include all profits of the company up to the date of distribution or payment referred to in those sub-`
  line `clauses, and in sub-clause ( c ) shall include all profits of the company up to the date of`
  line `liquidation, 6 [but shall not, where the liquidation is consequent on the compulsory acquisition of its`
  line `undertaking by the Government or a corporation owned or controlled by the Government under any`
  line `law for the time being in force, include any profits of the company prior to three successive previous`
  line `years immediately preceding the previous year in which such acquisition took place].`
  line `7 [ Explanation 2A. –– In the case of an amalgamated company, the accumulated profits, whether`
  line `capitalised or not, or loss, as the case may be, shall be increased by the accumulated profits, whether`
  line `capitalised or not, of the amalgamating company on the date of amalgamation.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 3, for “by way of advance or loan to a shareholder, being a person who has a substantial`
  line `interest in the company,” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 13 of 1966, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1966).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 31 of 1964, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
