obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line 41
  line `1 [ Explanation 3. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( a ) “ concern ” means a Hindu undivided family, or a firm or an association of persons or a`
  line `body of individuals or a company;`
  line `( b ) a person shall be deemed to have a substantial interest in a concern, other than a company,`
  line `if he is, at any time during the previous year, beneficially entitled to not less than twenty per cent.`
  line `of the income of such concern;]`
  line `2 [( 22A ) “ domestic company ” means an Indian company, or any other company which, in respect`
  line `of its income liable to tax under this Act, has made the prescribed arrangements for the declaration`
  line `and payment, within India, of the dividends (including dividends on preference shares) payable out of`
  line `such income;]`
  line `3 [( 22AA ) “ document ” includes an electronic record as defined in clause ( t ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 2 of the Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000);]`
  line `4 [( 22AAA ) “electoral trust” means a trust so approved by the Board in accordance with the`
  line `scheme made in this regard by the Central Government;]`
  line `5 [ 6 [( 22B )] “ fair market value ”, in relation to a capital asset, means —`
  line `( i ) the price that the capital asset would ordinarily fetch on sale in the open market on the`
  line `relevant date; and`
  line `( ii ) where the price referred to in sub-clause ( i ) is not ascertainable, such price as may be`
  line `determined in accordance with the rules made under this Act;`
  line `7 [( 23 ) ( i ) “ firm ” shall have the meaning assigned to it in the Indian Partnership`
  line `Act, 1932 (9 of 1932), and shall include a limited liability partnership as defined in the Limited`
  line `Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009);`
  line `( ii ) “partner” shall have the meaning assigned to it in the Indian Partnership`
  line `Act, 1932 (9 of 1932), and shall include, —`
  line `( a ) any person who, being a minor, has been admitted to the benefits of partnership; and`
  line `( b ) a partner of a limited liability partnership as defined in the Limited Liability Partnership`
  line `Act, 2008 (6 of 2009);`
  line `( iii ) “ partnership ” shall have the meaning assigned to it in the Indian Partnership`
  line `Act, 1932 (9 of 1932), and shall include a limited liability partnership as defined in the Limited`
  line `Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009);`
  line `2 [( 23A ) “ foreign company ” means a company which is not a domestic company;]`
  line `8 [( 23B ) “ fringe benefits ” means any fringe benefits referred to in section 115WB;]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989.`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-6-2001).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 5 of 1964, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1964).`
  line `6. Clause ( 22A ) renumbered as clause ( 22B ) thereof by Act 4 of 1988, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 3, for clause ( 23 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
