  line 42
  line `1 [( 23C ) “ hearing ” includes communication of data and documents through electronic mode;]`
  line `( 24 ) “ income ” includes —`
  line `( i ) profits and gains;`
  line `( ii ) dividend;`
  line `2 [( iia ) voluntary contributions received by a trust created wholly or partly for charitable or`
  line `religious purposes or by an institution established wholly or partly for such purposes 3 [or by an`
  line `association or institution referred to in clause ( 21 ) or clause ( 23 ), or by a fund or trust or`
  line `institution referred to in sub-clause ( iv ) or sub-clause ( v ) 4 [or by any university or other`
  line `educational institution referred to in sub-clause ( iiiad ) or sub-clause ( vi ) or by any hospital or`
  line `other institution referred to in sub-clause ( iiiae ) or sub-clause ( via )] of clause ( 23C ), of`
  line `section 10 ] 5 [or by an electoral trust].]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-clause, “ trust ” includes any other legal obligation;]`
  line `( iii ) the value of any perquisite or profit in lieu of salary taxable under clauses ( 2 ) and ( 3 )`
  line `of section 17;`
  line `6 [( iiia ) any special allowance or benefit, other than perquisite included under sub-clause ( iii ),`
  line `specifically granted to the assessee to meet expenses wholly, necessarily and exclusively for the`
  line `performance of the duties of an office or employment of profit;`
  line `( iiib ) any allowance granted to the assessee either to meet his personal expenses at the place`
  line `where the duties of his office or employment of profit are ordinarily performed by him or at a`
  line `place where he ordinarily resides or to compensate him for the increased cost of living;]`
  line `( iv ) the value of any benefit or perquisite, whether convertible into money or not, obtained`
  line `from a company either by a director or by a person who has a substantial interest in the company,`
  line `or by a relative of the director or such person, and any sum paid by any such company in respect`
  line `of any obligation which, but for such payment, would have been payable by the director or other`
  line `person aforesaid;`
  line `7 [( iva ) the value of any benefit or perquisite, whether convertible into money or not, obtained`
  line `by any representative assessee mentioned in clause ( iii ) or clause ( iv ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section`
  line `160 or by any person on whose behalf or for whose benefit any income is receivable by the`
  line `representative assessee (such person being hereafter in this sub-clause referred to as the`
  line `“ beneficiary ” ) and any sum paid by the representative assessee in respect of any obligation`
  line `which, but for such payment, would have been payable by the beneficiary;]`
  line `( v ) any sum chargeable to income-tax under clauses ( ii ) and ( iii ) of section 28 or`
  line `section 41 or section 59;`
  line `8 [( va ) any sum chargeable to income-tax under clause ( iiia ) of section 28;]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
