obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line 47
  line `( iii ) a company,`
  line `( iv ) a firm,`
  line `( v ) an association of persons or a body of individuals, whether incorporated or not,`
  line `( vi ) a local authority, and`
  line `( vii ) every artificial juridical person, not falling within any of the preceding sub-clauses.`
  line `1 [Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, an association of persons or a body of`
  line `individuals or a local authority or an artificial juridical person shall be deemed to be a person,`
  line `whether or not such person or body or authority or juridical person was formed or established or`
  line `incorporated with the object of deriving income, profits or gains;]`
  line `( 32 ) “person who has a substantial interest in the company”, in relation to a company, means a`
  line `person who is the beneficial owner of shares, not being shares entitled to a fixed rate of dividend`
  line `whether with or without a right to participate in profits, carrying not less than twenty per cent. of the`
  line `voting power;`
  line `( 33 ) “prescribed” means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line `( 34 ) “previous year” means the previous year as defined in section 3;`
  line `2 [( 34A ) “Principal Chief Commissioner of Income -tax ” means a person appointed to be a`
  line `Principal Chief Commissioner of Income-tax under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 117;`
  line `( 34B ) “Principal Commissioner of Income - tax” means a person appointed to be a Principal`
  line `Commissioner of Income-tax under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 117;`
  line `( 34C ) “Principal Director of Income - tax” means a person appointed to be a Principal Director of`
  line `Income-tax under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 117;`
  line `( 34D ) “Principal Director General of Income - tax” means a person appointed to be a Principal`
  line `Director General of Income-tax under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 117;]`
  line `( 35 ) “principal officer”, used with reference to a local authority or a company or any other public`
  line `body or any association of persons or any body of individuals, means —`
  line `( a ) the secretary, treasurer, manager or agent of the authority, company, association or body,`
  line or
  line `( b ) any person connected with the management or administration of the local authority,`
  line `company, association or body upon whom the 3 [Assessing Officer] has served a notice of his`
  line `intention of treating him as the principal officer thereof;`
  line `( 36 ) “profession” includes vocation;`
  line `4 [( 36A ) “public sector company” means any corporation established by or under any Central,`
  line `State or Provincial Act or a Government company as defined in section 617 of the Companies Act,`
  line `1956 (1 of 1956);]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 3 (w.r.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
