  line 52
  line `1 [ Explanation 4. —For the purposes of this clause, the expression “equity oriented fund” shall`
  line `have the meaning assigned to it in 2 [clause ( a ) of the Explanation to section 112A];]`
  line `3 [( 42B ) “short - term capital gain” means capital gain arising from the transfer of a short-term`
  line `capital asset;]`
  line `4 [( 42C ) “slump sale” means the transfer of one or more undertakings as a result of the sale for a`
  line `lump sum consideration without values being assigned to the individual assets and liabilities in such`
  line sales.
  line `Explanation 1. — For the purposes of this clause, “undertaking” shall have the meaning assigned`
  line `to it in Explanation 1 to clause ( 19AA ).`
  line `Explanation 2. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the determination of the`
  line `value of an asset or liability for the sole purpose of payment of stamp duty, registration fees or other`
  line `similar taxes or fees shall not be regarded as assignment of values to individual assets or liabilities;]`
  line `5 [( 43 ) “tax” in relation to the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1965, and any`
  line `subsequent assessment year means income-tax chargeable under the provisions of this Act, and in`
  line `relation to any other assessment year income-tax and super-tax chargeable under the provisions of`
  line `this Act prior to the aforesaid date 6 [and in relation to the assessment year commencing on the 1st day`
  line `of April, 2006, and any subsequent assessment year includes the fringe benefit tax payable`
  line `under section 115WA];`
  line `( 43A ) “tax credit certificate” means a tax credit certificate granted to any person in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of Chapter XXII-B and any scheme made thereunder;]`
  line `7 * * * * *`
  line `8 [( 44 ) “Tax Recovery Officer” means any Income -tax Officer who may be authorised by the`
  line `9 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 10 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner], by general or special order in writing, to exercise the powers of a Tax Recovery`
  line `Officer 11 [and also to exercise or perform such powers and functions which are conferred on, or`
  line `assigned to, an Assessing Officer under this Act and which may be prescribed];]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 3, for “ the Explanation to clause ( 38 ) of section 10 ” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2019).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 4, for clause ( 43 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 3, for “the aforesaid date” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `7. Clause ( 43B ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clause ( 44 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `10. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `11. Ins. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 2 (w.e.f. 13-7-2006).`
