obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line 53
  line `( 45 ) “total income” means the total amount of income referred to in section 5, computed in the`
  line `manne r laid down in this Act;`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `2 [( 47 ) “transfer”, in relation to a capital asset, includes,—`
  line `( i ) the sale, exchange or relinquishme nt of the asset; or`
  line `( ii ) the extinguishment of any rights therein; or`
  line `( iii ) the compulsory acquisition thereof under any law; or`
  line `( iv ) in a case where the asset is converted by the owner thereof into, or is treated by him as,`
  line `stock-in-trade of a business carried on by him, such conversion or treatment;] 3 [or]`
  line `4 [( iva ) the maturity or redemption of a zero coupon bond; or]`
  line `3 [( v ) any transaction involving the allowing of the possession of any immovable property to`
  line `be taken or retained in part performance of a contract of the nature referred to in section 53A of`
  line `the Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882); or`
  line `( vi ) any transaction (whether by way of becoming a member of, or acquiring shares in, a`
  line `co-operative society, company or other association of persons or by way of any agreement or any`
  line `arrangement or in any other manner whatsoever) which has the effect of transferring, or enabling`
  line `the enjoyment of, any immovable property.`
  line `5 [ Explanation 1 ]. — For the purposes of sub-clauses ( v ) and ( vi ), “immovable property” shall have`
  line `the same meaning as in clause ( d ) of section 269UA.]`
  line `6 [ Explanation 2. —For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that “transfer” includes and`
  line `shall be deemed to have always included disposing of or parting with an asset or any interest therein,`
  line `or creating any interest in any asset in any manner whatsoever, directly or indirectly, absolutely or`
  line `conditionally, voluntarily or involuntarily, by way of an agreement (whether entered into in India or`
  line `outside India) or otherwise, notwithstanding that such transfer of rights has been characterised as`
  line `being effected or dependent upon or flowing from the transfer of a share or shares of a company`
  line `registered or incorporated outside India;]`
  line `7 [( 48 ) “zero coupon bond” means a bond—`
  line `( a ) issued by any infrastructure capital company or infrastructure capital fund or public sector`
  line `company 8 [or scheduled bank] on or after the 1st day of June, 2005;`
  line `( b ) in respect of which no payment and benefit is received or receivable before maturity or`
  line `redemption from infrastructure capital company or infrastructure capital fund or public sector`
  line `company 8 [or scheduled bank]; and`
  line `( c ) which the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this`
  line behalf.
  line `1. Clause ( 46 ) omitted by Act 10 of 1965, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 2, for clause ( 47 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `5. The Explanation renumbered as Explanation 1 by Act 23 of 2012, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `6. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006). Earlier clause ( 48 ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989) and later`
  line `restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989) and again omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
