  sourcePage 54
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line 54
  line `1 [ Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, the expression “scheduled bank” shall have the`
  line `meaning assigned to it in clause ( ii ) of the Explanation to sub-clause ( c ) of clause ( viia ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 36.]]`
  line `2 [ 3. “Previous year” defined. —For the purposes of this Act, “previous year” means the financial`
  line `year immediately preceding the assessment year:`
  line `Provided that, in the case of a business or profession newly set up, or a source of income newly`
  line `coming into existence, in the said financial year, the previous year shall be the period beginning with the`
  line `date of setting up of the business or profession or, as the case may be, the date on which the source of`
  line `income newly comes into existence and ending with the said financial year.]`
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `B ASIS OF C HARGE`
  line `4. Charge of income-tax. — ( 1 ) Where any Central Act enacts that income-tax shall be charged for`
  line `any assessment year at any rate or rates, income-tax at that rate or those rates shall be charged for that`
  line `year in accordance with, and 3 [subject to the provisions (including provisions for the levy of additional`
  line `income-tax) of, this Act] in respect of the total income of the previous year 4 ***of every person:`
  line `Provided that where by virtue of any provision of this Act income-tax is to be charged in respect of`
  line `the income of a period other than the previous year, income-tax shall be charged accordingly.`
  line `( 2 ) In respect of income chargeable under sub-section ( 1 ), income-tax shall be deducted at the source`
  line `or paid in advance, where it is so deductible or payable under any provision of this Act.`
  line `5. Scope of total income. — ( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the total income of any previous`
  line `year of a person who is a resident includes all income from whatever source derived which —`
  line `( a ) is received or is deemed to be received in India in such year by or on behalf of such person;`
  line or
  line `( b ) accrues or arises or is deemed to accrue or arise to him in India during such year; or`
  line `( c ) accrues or arises to him outside India during such year:`
  line `Provided that, in the case of a person not ordinarily resident in India within the meaning of`
  line `sub-section ( 6 ) of section 6, the income which accrues or arises to him outside India shall not be so`
  line `included unless it is derived from a business controlled in or a profession set up in India.`
  line `( 2 ) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the total income of any previous year of a person who is a`
  line `non-resident includes all income from whatever source derived which —`
  line `( a ) is received or is deemed to be received in India in such year by or on behalf of such`
  line `person; or`
  line `( b ) accrues or arises or is deemed to accrue or arise to him in India during such year.`
  line `Explanation 1. — Income accruing or arising outside India shall not be deemed to be received in India`
  line `within the meaning of this section by reason only of the fact that it is taken into account in a balance sheet`
  line `prepared in India.`
  line `Explanation 2. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that income which has been`
  line `included in the total income of a person on the basis that it has accrued or arisen or is deemed to have`
  line `accrued or arisen to him shall not again be so included on the basis that it is received or deemed to be`
  line `received by him in India.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 5, for “subject to the provisions of this Act” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `4. The words “or previous years, as the case may be” o mitted by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
