  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  sourcePage 56
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line 56
  line `1 [( 3 ) A company is said to be a resident in India in any previous year, if —`
  line `( i ) it is an Indian company; or`
  line `( ii ) its place of effective management, in that year, is in India.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause “place of effective management” means a place`
  line `where key management and commercial decisions that are necessary for the conduct of business of an`
  line `entity as a whole are, in substance made.]`
  line `( 4 ) Every other person is said to be resident in India in any previous year in every case, except`
  line `where during that year the control and management of his affairs is situated wholly outside India.`
  line `( 5 ) If a person is resident in India in a previous year relevant to an assessment year in respect of`
  line `any source of income, he shall be deemed to be resident in India in the previous year relevant to the`
  line `assessment year in respect of each of his other sources of income.`
  line `2 [( 6 ) A person is said to be “not ordinarily resident” in India in any previous year if such person`
  line `is —`
  line `( a ) an individual who has been a non-resident in India in nine out of the ten previous years`
  line `preceding that year, or has during the seven previous years preceding that year been in India for a`
  line `period of, or periods amounting in all to, seven hundred and twenty-nine days or less; or`
  line `( b ) a Hindu undivided family whose manager has been a non-resident in India in nine out of`
  line `the ten previous years preceding that year, or has during the seven previous years preceding that`
  line `year been in India for a period of, or periods amounting in all to, seven hundred and twenty-nine`
  line `days or less.]`
  line `7. Income deemed to be received. — The following incomes shall be deemed to be received in the`
  line `previous year: —`
  line `( i ) the annual accretion in the previous year to the balance at the credit of an employee`
  line `participating in a recognised provident fund, to the extent provided in rule 6 of Part A of the Fourth`
  line Schedule;
  line `( ii ) the transferred balance in a recognised provident fund, to the extent provided in sub-rule (4)`
  line `of rule 11 of Part A of the Fourth Schedule;`
  line `3 [( iii ) the contribution made, by the Central Government 4 [or any other employer] in the previous`
  line `year, to the account of an employee under a pension scheme referred to in section 80CCD.]`
  line `8. Dividend income. — 5 [For the purposes of inclusion in the total income of an assessee, —`
  line `( a ) any dividend] declared by a company or distributed or paid by it within the meaning of`
  line `sub-clause ( a ) or sub-clause ( b ) or sub-clause ( c ) or sub-clause ( d ) or sub-clause ( e ) of clause ( 22 )`
  line `of section 2 shall be deemed to be the income of the previous year in which it is so declared,`
  line `distributed or paid, as the case may be;`
  line `6 [( b ) any interim dividend shall be deemed to be the income of the previous year in which the`
  line `amount of such dividend is unconditionally made available by the company to the member who is`
  line `entitled to it.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 4, for clause ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 4, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 5, for “For the purposes of inclusion in the total income of an assessee, any dividend”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `6. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
