  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  sourcePage 58
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line 58
  line `1 [( a ) has and habitually exercises in India, an authority to conclude contracts on behalf of the`
  line `non-resident or habitually concludes contracts or habitually plays the principal role leading to`
  line `conclusion of contracts by that non-resident and the contracts are ––`
  line `( i ) in the name of the non-resident; or`
  line `( ii ) for the transfer of the ownership of, or for the granting of the right to use, property`
  line `owned by that non-resident or that non-resident has the right to use; or`
  line `( iii ) for the provision of services by the non-resident; or]`
  line `( b ) has no such authority, but habitually maintains in India a stock of goods or merchandise`
  line `from which he regularly delivers goods or merchandise on behalf of the non-resident; or`
  line `( c ) habitually secures orders in India, mainly or wholly for the non-resident or for that`
  line `non-resident and other non-residents controlling, controlled by, or subject to the same common`
  line `control, as that non-resident:`
  line `Provided that such business connection shall not include any business activity carried out`
  line `through a broker, general commission agent or any other agent having an independent status, if`
  line `such broker, general commission agent or any other agent having an independent status is acting`
  line `in the ordinary course of his business:`
  line `Provided further that where such broker, general commission agent or any other agent works`
  line `mainly or wholly on behalf of a non-resident (hereafter in this proviso referred to as the principal`
  line `non-resident) or on behalf of such non-resident and other non-residents which are controlled by`
  line `the principal non-resident or have a controlling interest in the principal non-resident or are subject`
  line `to the same common control as the principal non-resident, he shall not be deemed to be a broker,`
  line `general commission agent or an agent of an independent status.`
  line `2 [ Explanation 2A. –– For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that the significant economic`
  line `presence of a non- resident in India shall constitute “business connection” in India and “significant`
  line `economic presence” for this purpose, shall mean––`
  line `( a ) transaction in respect of any goods, services or property carried out by a non-resident in`
  line `India including provision of download of data or software in India, if the aggregate of payments`
  line `arising from such transaction or transactions during the previous year exceeds such amount as`
  line `may be prescribed; or`
  line `( b ) systematic and continuous soliciting of business activities or engaging in interaction with`
  line `such number of users as may be prescribed, in India through digital means:`
  line `Provided that the transactions or activities shall constitute significant economic presence in`
  line `India, whether or not, —`
  line `( i ) the agreement for such transactions or activities is entered in India;`
  line `( ii ) the non-resident has a residence or place of business in India; or`
  line `( iii ) the non-resident renders services in India:`
  line `Provided further that only so much of income as is attributable to the transactions or`
  line `activities referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) shall be deemed to accrue or arise in India.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 4, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-59
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Page 59`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  sourcePage 59
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line 59
  line `Explanation 3. — Where a business is carried on in India through a person referred to in clause ( a )`
  line `or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ) of Explanation 2, only so much of income as is attributable to the`
  line `operations carried out in India shall be deemed to accrue or arise in India.]`
  line `1 [ Explanation 4. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that the expression “through”`
  line `shall mean and include and shall be deemed to have always meant and included “by means of”, “in`
  line `consequence of” or “by reason of”.`
  line `Explanation 5. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that an asset or a capital asset`
  line `being any share or interest in a company or entity registered or incorporated outside India shall be`
  line `deemed to be and shall always be deemed to have been situated in India, if the share or interest`
  line `derives, directly or indirectly, its value substantially from the assets located in India:]`
  line `2 [Provided that nothing contained in this Explanation shall apply to an asset or capital asset, which is`
  line `held by a non-resident by way of investment, directly or indirectly, in a Foreign Institutional Investor as`
  line `referred to in clause ( a ) of the Explanation to section 115AD for an assessment year commencing on or`
  line `after the 1st day of April, 2012 but before the 1st day of April, 2015:]`
  line `3 [Provided further that nothing contained in this Explanation shall apply to an asset or capital asset,`
  line `which is held by a non-resident by way of investment, directly or indirectly, in Category-I or Category-II`
  line `foreign portfolio investor under the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Foreign Portfolio Investors)`
  line `Regulations, 2014, made under the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992.]`
  line `4 [ Explanation 6. — For the purposes of this clause, it is hereby declared that —`
  line `( a ) the share or interest, referred to in Explanation 5, shall be deemed to derive its value`
  line `substantially from the assets (whether tangible or intangible) located in India, if, on the specified`
  line `date, the value of such assets —`
  line `( i ) exceeds the amount of ten crore rupees; and`
  line `( ii ) represents at least fifty per cent. of the value of all the assets owned by the company`
  line `or entity, as the case may be;`
  line `( b ) the value of an asset shall be the fair market value as on the specified date, of such asset`
  line `without reduction of liabilities, if any, in respect of the asset, determined in such manner as may`
  line `be prescribed;`
  line `( c ) “accounting period” means each period of twelve months ending with the 31st day of`
  line `March:`
  line `Provided that where a company or an entity, referred to in Explanation 5, regularly adopts a`
  line `period of twelve months ending on a day other than the 31st day of March for the purpose of —`
  line `( i ) complying with the provisions of the tax laws of the territory, of which it is a`
  line `resident, for tax purposes; or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `2. The proviso inserted by Act 7 of 2017, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2012).`
  line `3. The proviso inserted by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
