  sourcePage 61
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line 61
  line `( b ) the rest period or leave period which is preceded and succeeded by services rendered in`
  line `India and forms part of the service contract of employment,`
  line `shall be regarded as income earned in India;]`
  line `( iii ) income chargeable under the head “ Salaries ” payable by the Government to a citizen of India`
  line `for service outside India;`
  line `( iv ) a dividend paid by an Indian company outside India;`
  line `1 [( v ) income by way of interest payable by —`
  line `( a ) the Government; or`
  line `( b ) a person who is a resident, except where the interest is payable in respect of any debt`
  line `incurred, or moneys borrowed and used, for the purposes of a business or profession carried on`
  line `by such person outside India or for the purposes of making or earning any income from any`
  line `source outside India; or`
  line `( c ) a person who is a non-resident, where the interest is payable in respect of any debt`
  line `incurred, or moneys borrowed and used, for the purposes of a business or profession carried on`
  line `by such person in India;`
  line `2 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( a ) it is hereby declared that in the case of a non-resident, being a person engaged in the`
  line `business of banking, any interest payable by the permanent establishment in India of such`
  line `non-resident to the head office or any permanent establishment or any other part of such`
  line `non-resident outside India shall be deemed to accrue or arise in India and shall be chargeable to`
  line `tax in addition to any income attributable to the permanent establishment in India and the`
  line `permanent establishment in India shall be deemed to be a person separate and independent of the`
  line `non-resident person of which it is a permanent establishment and the provisions of the Act`
  line `relating to computation of total income, determination of tax and collection and recovery shall`
  line `apply accordingly;`
  line `( b ) “permanent establishment” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( iiia ) of`
  line `section 92F;]`
  line `( vi ) income by way of royalty payable by —`
  line `( a ) the Government; or`
  line `( b ) a person who is a resident, except where the royalty is payable in respect of any right,`
  line `property or information used or services utilised for the purposes of a business or profession`
  line `carried on by such person outside India or for the purposes of making or earning any income from`
  line `any source outside India; or`
  line `( c ) a person who is a non-resident, where the royalty is payable in respect of any right,`
  line `property or information used or services utilised for the purposes of a business or profession`
  line `carried on by such person in India or for the purposes of making or earning any income from any`
  line `source in India:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall apply in relation to so much of the income`
  line `by way of royalty as consists of lump sum consideration for the transfer outside India of, or the`
  line `imparting of information outside India in respect of, any data, documentation, drawing or`
  line `specification relating to any patent, invention, model, design, secret formula or process or trade`
  line `mark or similar property, if such income is payable in pursuance of an agreement made before the`
  line `1st day of April, 1976, and the agreement is approved by the Central Government:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 66 of 1976, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-6-1976).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
