  title `Page 62`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  sourcePage 62
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line 62
  line `1 [Provided further that nothing contained in this clause shall apply in relation to so much of the`
  line `income by way of royalty as consists of lump sum payment made by a person, who is a resident, for`
  line `the transfer of all or any rights (including the granting of a licence) in respect of computer software`
  line `supplied by a non-resident manufacturer along with a computer or computer-based equipment under`
  line `any scheme approved under the Policy on Computer Software Export, Software Development and`
  line `Training, 1986 of the Government of India.]`
  line `Explanation 1. — For the purposes of the 2 [first proviso], an agreement made on or after the 1st`
  line `day of April, 1976, shall be deemed to have been made before that date if the agreement is made in`
  line `accordance with proposals approved by the Central Government before that date; so, however, that,`
  line `where the recipient of the income by way of royalty is a foreign company, the agreement shall not be`
  line `deemed to have been made before that date unless, before the expiry of the time allowed under sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) of section 139 (whether fixed originally or on extension) for furnishing`
  line `the return of income for the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1977, or the`
  line `assessment year in respect of which such income first becomes chargeable to tax under this Act,`
  line `whichever assessment year is later, the company exercises an option by furnishing a declaration in`
  line `writing to the 3 [Assessing Officer] (such option being final for that assessment year and for every`
  line `subsequent assessment year) that the agreement may be regarded as an agreement made before the 1st`
  line `day of April, 1976.`
  line `Explanation 2. — For the purposes of this clause, “ royalty ” means consideration (including any`
  line `lump sum consideration but excluding any consideration which would be the income of the recipient`
  line `chargeable under the head “ Capital gains ” ) for —`
  line `( i ) the transfer of all or any rights (including the granting of a licence) in respect of a patent,`
  line `invention, model, design, secret formula or process or trade mark or similar property;`
  line `( ii ) the imparting of any information concerning the working of, or the use of, a patent,`
  line `invention, model, design, secret formula or process or trade mark or similar property;`
  line `( iii ) the use of any patent, invention, model, design, secret formula or process or trade mark`
  line `or similar property;`
  line `( iv ) the imparting of any information concerning technical, industrial, commercial or`
  line `scientific knowledge, experience or skill;`
  line `4 [( iva ) the use or right to use any industrial, commercial or scientific equipment but not`
  line `including the amounts referred to in section 44BB;]`
  line `( v ) the transfer of all or any rights (including the granting of a licence) in respect of any`
  line `copyright, literary, artistic or scientific work including films or video tapes for use in connection`
  line `with television or tapes for use in connection with radio broadcasting, but not including`
  line `consideration for the sale, distribution or exhibition of cinematographic films; or`
  line `( vi ) the rendering of any services in connection with the activities referred to in sub-clauses`
  line `( i ) to ( iv ), ( iva ) and ( v ).`
  line `5 [ Explanation 3. — For the purposes of this clause, “computer software” means any computer`
  line `programme recorded on any disc, tape, perforated media or other information storage device and`
  line `includes any such programme or any customized electronic data.]`
  line `6 [ Explanation 4. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that the transfer of all or any`
  line `rights in respect of any right, property or information includes and has always included transfer of all`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “foregoing proviso” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1991).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 4, for Explanation 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-6-1976).`
