  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  sourcePage 63
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line 63
  line `or any right for use or right to use a computer software (including granting of a licence) irrespective`
  line `of the medium through which such right is transferred.`
  line `Explanation 5. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that the royalty includes and has`
  line `always included consideration in respect of any right, property or information, whether or not —`
  line `( a ) the possession or control of such right, property or information is with the payer;`
  line `( b ) such right, property or information is used directly by the payer;`
  line `( c ) the location of such right, property or information is in India.]`
  line `Explanation 6. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that the expression “ process ”`
  line `includes and shall be deemed to have always included transmission by satellite (including up-linking,`
  line `amplification, conversion for down-linking of any signal), cable, optic fibre or by any other similar`
  line `technology, whether or not such process is secret;]`
  line `( vii ) income by way of fees for technical services payable by —`
  line `( a ) the Government; or`
  line `( b ) a person who is a resident, except where the fees are payable in respect of services`
  line `utilised in a business or profession carried on by such person outside India or for the purposes of`
  line `making or earning any income from any source outside India; or`
  line `( c ) a person who is a non-resident, where the fees are payable in respect of services utilised in`
  line `a business or profession carried on by such person in India or for the purposes of making or`
  line `earning any income from any source in India:`
  line `1 [Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall apply in relation to any incomebyway of`
  line `fees for technical services payable in pursuance of an agreement made before the 1st day of April,`
  line `1976, and approved by the Central Government.]`
  line `2 [ Explanation 1. — For the purposes of the foregoing proviso, an agreement made on or after the`
  line `1st day of April, 1976, shall be deemed to have been made before that date if the agreement is made`
  line `in accordance with proposals approved by the Central Government before that date.]`
  line `Explanation 3 [2]. —For the purposes of this clause, “fees for technical services” means any`
  line `consideration (including any lump sum consideration) for the rendering of any managerial, technical`
  line `or consultancy services (including the provision of services of technical or other personnel) but does`
  line `not include consideration for any construction, assembly, mining or like project undertaken by the`
  line `recipient or consideration which would be income of the recipient chargeable under the head`
  line “Salaries”.
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), any pension payable outside India to a`
  line `person residing permanently outside India shall not be deemed to accrue or arise in India, if the`
  line `pension is payable to a person referred to in article 314 of the Constitution or to a person who, having`
  line `been appointed before the 15th day of August, 1947, to be a Judge of the Federal Court or of a High`
  line `Court within the meaning of the Government of India Act, 1935, continues to serve on or after the`
  line `commencement of the Constitution as a Judge in India.`
  line `Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that for the purposes of this`
  line `section, income of a non-resident shall be deemed to accrue or arise in India under clause ( v ) or clause`
  line `( vi ) or clause ( vii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) and shall be included in the total income of the non-resident,`
  line `whether or not, —`
  line `( i ) the non-resident has a residence or place of business or business connection in India; or`
  line `( ii ) the non-resident has rendered services in India.`
  line `1. The proviso ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1977).`
  line `2. Explanation ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1977).`
  line `3. Explanation renumbered as Explanation 2 thereof by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1977).`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
