obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line 66
  line `( 2 ) 1 [subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 64,] any sum received by an individual`
  line `as a member of a Hindu undivided family, where such sum has been paid out of the income of the`
  line `family, or, in the case of any impartible estate, where such sum has been paid out of the income of the`
  line `estate belonging to the family;`
  line `2 [( 2A ) in the case of a person being a partner of a firm which is separately assessed as such, his`
  line `share in the total income of the firm.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, the share of a partner in the total income of a firm`
  line `separately assessed as such shall, notwithstanding anything contained in any other law, be an amount`
  line `which bears to the total income of the firm the same proportion as the amount of his share in the`
  line `profits of the firm in accordance with the partnership deed bears to such profits;]`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 [( 4 ) ( i ) in the case of a non-resident, any income by way of interest on such securities or bonds as`
  line `the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf, including`
  line `income by way of premium on the redemption of such bonds:`
  line `5 [Provided that the Central Government shall not specify, for the purposes of this sub-clause, such`
  line `securities or bonds on or after the 1st day of June, 2002;]`
  line `6 [( ii ) in the case of an individual, any income by way of interest on moneys standing to his credit`
  line `in a Non-Resident (External) Account in any bank in India in accordance with 7 [the Foreign`
  line `Exchange Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999)], and the rules made thereunder:`
  line `Provided that such individual is a person resident outside India as defined in 8 [clause ( w )]`
  line `ofsection 2of the said Act or is a person who has been permitted by the Reserve Bank of India to`
  line `maintain the aforesaid Account;]]`
  line `9 * * * * *`
  line `10 [( 4B ) in the case of an individual, being a citizen of India or a person of Indian origin, who is a`
  line `non-resident, any income from interest on such 11 [savings certificates issued before the 1st day of`
  line `June, 2002] by the Central Government as that Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify in this behalf:`
  line `Provided that the individual has subscribed to such certificates in convertible foreign exchange`
  line `remitted from a country outside India in accordance with the provisions of 7 [the Foreign Exchange`
  line `Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999)], and any rules made thereunder.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( a ) a person shall be deemed to be of Indian origin if he, or either of his parents or any of his`
  line `grandparents, was born in undivided India;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993). Earliar inserted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 6 and omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Clause ( 3 ) omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 6, for clauses ( 4 ) and ( 4A ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 5, for sub-clause ( ii ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 4, for “the Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 6, for “cla use ( q )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `9. The Second proviso omitted by Act 18 of 2005, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 14 of 1982, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1983).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 4, for “savings certificates issued” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2003).`
