obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line 67
  line `( b ) “co nvertible foreign exchange” means foreign exchange which is for the time being`
  line `treated by the Reserve Bank of India as convertible foreign exchange for the purposes of 1 [the`
  line `Foreign Exchange Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999)], and any rules made thereunder;]`
  line `2 [( 5 ) in the case of an individual, the value of any travel concession or assistance received by, or`
  line `due to, him, —`
  line `( a ) from his employer for himself and his family, in connection with his proceeding on leave`
  line `to any place in India;`
  line `( b ) from his employer or former employer for himself and his family, in connection with his`
  line `proceeding to any place in India after retirement from service or after the termination of his`
  line service,
  line `subject to such conditions as may be prescribed(including conditions as to number of journeys and`
  line `the amount which shall be exempt per head) having regard to the travel concession or assistance`
  line `granted to the employees of the Central Government:`
  line `Provided that the amount exempt under this clause shall in no case exceed the amount of`
  line `expenses actually incurred for the purpose of such travel.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, “family”, in relation to an individual, means—`
  line `( i ) the spouse and children of the individual; and`
  line `( ii ) the parents, brothers and sisters of the individual or any of them, wholly or mainly`
  line `dependent on the individual;]`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `( 6 ) in the case of an individual who is not a citizen of India, —`
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `6 [( ii ) the remuneration received by him as an official, by whatever name called, of an`
  line `embassy, high commission, legation, commission, consulate or the trade representation of a`
  line `foreign State, or as a member of the staff of any of these officials, for service in such capacity:`
  line `Provided that the remuneration received by him as a trade commissioner or other official`
  line `representative in India of the Government of a foreign State (not holding office as such in an`
  line `honorary capacity), or as a member of the staff of any of those officials, shall be exempt only if`
  line `the remuneration of the corresponding officials or, as the case may be, members of the staff, if`
  line `any, of the Government resident for similar purposes in the country concerned enjoys a similar`
  line `exemption in that country:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 4, for “the Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 36 of 1989, s. 4, for clause ( 5 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Clause ( 5A ) omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `4. Clause ( 5B ) omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `5. Sub-clause ( i ) omitted by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 4, for sub-clauses ( ii ) to ( v ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
