obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line 68
  line `Provided further that such members of the staff are subjects of the country represented and are`
  line `not engaged in any business or profession or employment in India otherwise than as members of such`
  line staff;]
  line `( vi ) the remuneration received by him as an employee of a foreign enterprise for services`
  line `rendered by him during his stay in India, provided the following conditions are fulfilled —`
  line `( a ) the foreign enterprise is not engaged in any trade or business in India;`
  line `( b ) his stay in India does not exceed in the aggregate a period of ninety days in such`
  line `previous year; and`
  line `( c ) such remuneration is not liable to be deducted from the income of the employer`
  line `chargeable under this Act;`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `( viii ) any income chargeable under the head “Salaries” received by or due to any such`
  line `individual being a non-resident as remuneration for services rendered in connection with his`
  line `employment on a foreign ship where his total stay in India does not exceed in the aggregate a`
  line `period of ninety days in the previous year;`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `5 [( xi ) the remuneration received by him as an employee of the Government of a foreign State`
  line `during his stay in India in connection with his training in any establishment or office of, or in any`
  line `undertaking owned by, —`
  line `( i ) the Government; or`
  line `( ii ) any company in which the entire paid-up share capital is held by the Central`
  line `Government, or any State Government or Governments, or partly by the Central Government`
  line `and partly by one or more State Governments; or`
  line `( iii ) any company which is a subsidiary of a company referred to in item ( ii ); or`
  line `( iv ) any corporation established by or under a Central, State or Provincial Act; or`
  line `( v ) any society registered under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (14 of 1860), or`
  line `under any other corresponding law for the time being in force and wholly financed by the`
  line `Central Government, or any State Government or State Governments, or partly by the Central`
  line `Government and partly by one or more State Governments;]`
  line `6 [( 6A ) where in the case of a foreign company deriving income by way of royalty or fees for`
  line `technical services received from Government or an Indian concern in pursuance of an agreement`
  line `1. Sub-clause ( via ) omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `2. Sub-clause ( vii ) omitted by Act 38 of 1993, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `3. Sub-clause ( viia ) omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `4. Sub-clause ( ix ) and ( x ) omitted by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 66 of 1976, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 11 of 1983, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1984).`
