obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line 70
  line `1 [( 6C ) any income arising to such foreign company, as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf, 2 [by way of royalty or fees] for technical`
  line `services received in pursuance of an agreement entered into with that Government for providing`
  line `services in or outside India in projects connected with security of India;]`
  line `3 [( 6D ) any income arising to a non-resident, not being a company, or a foreign company, by way`
  line `of royalty from, or fees for technical services rendered in or outside India to, the National Technical`
  line `Research Organisation;]`
  line `( 7 ) any allowances or perquisites paid or allowed as such outside India by the Government to a`
  line `citizen of India for rendering service outside India;`
  line `( 8 ) in the case of an individual who is assigned to duties in India in connection with any`
  line `co-operative technical assistance programmes and projects in accordance with an agreement entered`
  line `into by the Central Government and the Government of a foreign State (the terms whereof provide for`
  line `the exemption given by this clause) —`
  line `( a ) the remuneration received by him directly or indirectly from the Government of that`
  line `foreign State for such duties, and`
  line `( b ) any other income of such individual which accrues or arises outside India, and is not`
  line `deemed to accrue or arise in India, in respect of which such individual is required to pay any`
  line `income or social security tax to the Government of that foreign State;`
  line `4 [( 8A ) in the case of a consultant —`
  line `( a ) any remuneration or fee received by him or it, directly or indirectly, out of the funds made`
  line `available to an international organisation [hereafter referred to in this clause and clause ( 8B ) as`
  line `the agency] under a technical assistance grant agreement between the agency and the Government`
  line `of a foreign State; and`
  line `( b ) any other income which accrues or arises to him or it outside India, and is not deemed to`
  line `accrue or arise in India, in respect of which such consultant is required to pay any income or`
  line `social security tax to the Government of the country of his or its origin.`
  line `Explanation. —In this clause, “consultant” means—`
  line `( i ) any individual, who is either not a citizen of India or, being a citizen of India, is not`
  line `ordinarily resident in India; or`
  line `( ii ) any other person, being a non-resident,`
  line `engaged by the agency for rendering technical services in India in connection with any technical`
  line `assistance programme or project, provided the following conditions are fulfilled, namely: —`
  line `( 1 ) the technical assistance is in accordance with an agreement entered into by the Central`
  line `Government and the agency; and`
  line `( 2 ) the agreement relating to the engagement of the consultant is approved by the prescribed`
  line `authorityfor the purposes of this clause;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 6, for “by way of fees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2004).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
