obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line 71
  line `( 8B ) in the case of an individual who is assigned to duties in India in connection with any`
  line `technical assistance programme and project in accordance with an agreement entered into by the`
  line `Central Government and the agency —`
  line `( a ) the remuneration received by him, directly or indirectly, for such duties from any`
  line `consultant referred to in clause ( 8A ); and`
  line `( b ) any other income of such individual which accrues or arises outside India, and is not`
  line `deemed to accrue or arise in India, in respect of which such individual is required to pay any`
  line `income or social security tax to the country of his origin, provided the following conditions are`
  line `fulfilled, namely: —`
  line `( i ) the individual is an employee of the consultant referred to in clause ( 8A ) and is either`
  line `not a citizen of India or, being a citizen of India, is not ordinarily resident in India; and`
  line `( ii ) the contract of service of such individual is approved by the prescribed`
  line `authority before the commencement of his service;]`
  line `( 9 ) the income of any member of the family of any such individual as is referred to in clause ( 8 )`
  line `1 [or clause ( 8A ) or, as the case may be, clause ( 8B )] accompanying him to India, which accrues or`
  line `arises outside India, and is not deemed to accrue or arise in India, in respect of which such member is`
  line `required to pay any income or social security tax to the Government of that foreign State 1 [or, as the`
  line `case may be, country of origin of such member];`
  line `2 [( 10 ) ( i ) any death-cum-retirement gratuity received under the revised Pension Rules of the`
  line `Central Government or, as the case may be, the Central Civil Services (Pension) Rules, 1972, or`
  line `under any similar scheme applicable to the members of the civil services of the Union or holders of`
  line `posts connected with defence or of civil posts under the Union (such members or holders being`
  line `persons not governed by the said Rules) or to the members of the all-India services or to the members`
  line `of the civil services of a State or holders of civil posts under a State or to the employees of a local`
  line `authority or any payment of retiring gratuity received under the Pension Code or Regulations`
  line `applicable to the members of the defence services;`
  line `( ii ) any gratuity received under the Payment of Gratuity Act, 1972 (39 of 1972), to the extent it`
  line `does not exceed an amount calculated in accordance with the provisions of sub-sections ( 2 ) and ( 3 ) of`
  line `section 4 of that Act;`
  line `( iii ) any other gratuity received by an employee on his retirement or on his becoming`
  line `incapacitated prior to such retirement or on termination of his employment, or any gratuity received`
  line `by his widow, children or dependants on his death, to the extent it does not, in either case, exceed`
  line `one-half month ’ s salary for each year of completed service, 3 [calculated on the basis of the average`
  line `salary for the ten months immediately preceding the month in which any such event occurs, subject to`
  line `such limit as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this`
  line `behalf having regard to the limit applicable in this behalf to the employees of that Government]:`
  line `Provided that where any gratuities referred to in this clause are received by an employee from`
  line `more than one employer in the same previous year, the aggregate amount exempt from income-tax`
  line `under this clause 4 [shall not exceed the limit so specified]:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 1974, s. 3, for clause (10) (w.e.f. 1-4-1975).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 6, for the certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 6, for clause ( 10 ), ibid, “shall not exceed thirty six thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
