obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line 72
  line `Provided further that where any such gratuity or gratuities was or were received in any one or`
  line `more earlier previous years also and the whole or any part of the amount of such gratuity or gratuities`
  line `was not included in the total income of the assessee of such previous year or years, the amount`
  line `exempt from income-tax under this clause 1 [shall not exceed the limit so specified] as reduced by the`
  line `amount or, as the case may be, the aggregate amount not included in the total income of any such`
  line `previous year or years.`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `Explanation. — 3 [In this clause, and in clause ( 10AA )], “salary” shall have the meaning assigned to`
  line `it in clause ( h ) of rule 2 of Part A of the Fourth Schedule;]`
  line `4 [( 10A ) ( i ) any payment in commutation of pension received under the Civil Pensions`
  line `(Commutation) Rules of the Central Government 5 [or under any similar scheme applicable to the`
  line `members of the civil services of the Union or holders of posts connected with defence or of civil posts`
  line `under the Union (such members or holders being persons not governed by the said Rules) or to the`
  line `members of the all-India services or to the members of the defence services or to the members of the`
  line `civil services of a State or holders of civil posts under a State or to the employees of a local authority]`
  line `or a corporation established by a Central, State or Provincial Act;`
  line `( ii ) any payment in commutation of pension received under any scheme of any other employer, to`
  line `the extent it does not exceed —`
  line `( a ) in a case where the employee receives any gratuity, the commuted value of one-third of`
  line `the pension which he is normally entitled to receive, and`
  line `( b ) in any other case, the commuted value of one-half of such pension,`
  line `such commuted value being determined having regard to the age of the recipient, the state of his`
  line `health, the rate of interest and officially recognised tables of mortality;`
  line `6 * * * * *`
  line `7 [( iii ) any payment in commutation of pension received from a fund under clause ( 23AAB );]`
  line `8 [( 10AA ) ( i ) any payment received by an employee of the Central Government or a State`
  line `Government as the cash equivalent of the leave salary in respect of the period of earned leave at his`
  line `credit at the time of his retirement 9 [whether on superannuation] or otherwise;`
  line `( ii ) any payment of the nature referred to in sub-clause ( i ) received by an employee, other than an`
  line `employee of the Central Government or a State Government, in respect of so much of the period of earned`
  line `leave at his credit at the time of his retirement 9 [whether on superannuation] or otherwise as does not`
  line `exceed 10 [ten months], calculated on the basis of the average salary drawn by the employee during`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s.6 for “shall not exceed thirty six thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `2. The third and fourth provisos omitted by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for “In this clause” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 15 of 1965, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 20 of 1974, s. 3 for the certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `6. The proviso omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1997).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 14 of 1982, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1978).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 4 for “on superannuation” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1978).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 6 for “eight months” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
