obj_root_law_sections_74:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-74
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Page 74`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  sourcePage 74
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line 74
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause —`
  line `( a ) compensation received by a workman at the time of the closing down of the undertaking`
  line `in which he is employed shall be deemed to be compensation received at the time of his`
  line retrenchment;
  line `( b ) compensation received by a workman, at the time of the transfer (whether by agreement`
  line `or by operation of law) of the ownership or management of the undertaking in which he is`
  line `employed from the employer in relation to that undertaking to a new employer, shall be deemed`
  line `to be compensation received at the time of his retrenchment if —`
  line `( i ) the service of the workman has been interrupted by such transfer; or`
  line `( ii ) the terms and conditions of service applicable to the workman after such transfer are`
  line `in any way less favourable to the workman than those applicable to him immediately before`
  line `the transfer; or`
  line `( iii ) the new employer is, under the terms of such transfer or otherwise, legally not liable`
  line `to pay to the workman, in the event of his retrenchment, compensation on the basis that his`
  line `service has been continuous and has not been interrupted by the transfer;`
  line `( c ) the expressions “employer” and “workman” shall have the same meanings as in the`
  line `Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947);]`
  line `1 [( 10BB ) any payments made under the Bhopal Gas Leak Disaster (Processing of Claims) Act,`
  line `1985 (21 of 1985), and any scheme framed thereunder except payment made to any assessee in`
  line `connection with the Bhopal Gas Leak Disaster to the extent such assessee has been allowed a`
  line `deduction under this Act on account of any loss or damage caused to him by such disaster;]`
  line `2 [( 10BC ) any amount received or receivable from the Central Government or a State Government`
  line `or a local authority by an individual or his legal heir by way of compensation on account of any`
  line `disaster, except the amount received or receivable to the extent such individual or his legal heir has`
  line `been allowed a deduction under this Act on account of any loss or damage caused by such disaster.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purpose s of this clause, the expression “disaster” shall have the meaning`
  line `assigned to it under clause ( d ) of section 2 of the Disaster Management Act, 2005 (53 of 2005);]`
  line `3 [( 10C ) 4 [any amount received or receivable by an employee of] —`
  line `( i ) a public sector company; or`
  line `( ii ) any other company; or`
  line `( iii ) an authority established under a Central, State or Provincial Act; or`
  line `( iv ) a local 5 [authority; or]`
  line `6 [( v ) a co-operative society; or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 38 of 1993, s. 3, for clause ( 10C ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 6 for “any amount received by an employe of” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2004).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 6, for “authority,” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1995).`
  line `6. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
