  line 75
  line `( vi ) a University established or incorporated by or under a Central, State or Provincial Act`
  line `and an institution declared to be a University under section 3 of the University Grants`
  line `Commission Act, 1956(3 of 1956); or`
  line `( vii ) an Indian Institute of Technology within the meaning of clause ( g ) of section 3 of the`
  line `Institutes of Technology Act, 1961 (59 of 1961); or`
  line `1 [( viia ) any State Government; or]`
  line `2 [( viib ) the Central Government; or]`
  line `3 [( viic ) an institution, having importance throughout India or in any State or States, as the`
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf; or]`
  line `( viii ) such institute of management as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, specify in this behalf,]`
  line `4 {on his 5 [voluntary retirement} or termination of his service, in accordance with any scheme or`
  line `schemes of voluntary retirement or in the case of a public sector company referred to in`
  line `sub-clause ( i ), a scheme of voluntary separation, to the extent such amount does not exceed five lakh`
  line `rupees]:`
  line `Provided that the schemes of the said companies or authorities 6 [or societies or Universities or the`
  line `Institutes referred to in sub-clauses ( vii ) and ( viii )], as the case may be, governing the payment of`
  line `such amount are framed in accordance with such guidelines (including inter alia criteria of economic`
  line `viability) as may be prescribed 7 ***:`
  line `Provided further that where exemption has been allowed to an employee under this clause for any`
  line `assessment year, no exemption thereunder shall be allowed to him in relation to any other assessment`
  line `year:]`
  line `8 [Provided also that where any relief has been allowed to an assessee under section 89 for any`
  line `assessment year in respect of any amount received or receivable on his voluntary retirement or`
  line `termination of service or voluntary separation, no exemption under this clause shall be allowed to him`
  line `in relation to such, or any other, assessment year;]`
  line `9 [( 10CC ) in the case of an employee, being an individual deriving income in the nature of a`
  line `perquisite, not provided for by way of monetary payment, within the meaning of clause ( 2 ) of section`
  line `17, the tax on such income actually paid by his employer, at the option of the employer, on behalf of`
  line `such employee, notwithstanding anything contained in section 200 of the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956);]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 5, ibid, (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 6, for “at the time of his voluntary retirement” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2004).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 5, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
  line `7. The certain words brackets and figures omitted by Act 10 of 2000, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
