  line 77
  line `( 11 ) any payment from a provident fund to which the Provident Funds Act, 1925 (19 of 1925),`
  line `applies 1 [or from any other provident fund set up by the Central Government and notified by it in this`
  line `behalf in the Official Gazette];`
  line `2 [( 11A ) any payment from an account, opened in accordance with the Sukanya Samriddhi`
  line `Account Rules, 2014 made under the Government Savings Bank Act, 1873 (5 of 1873);]`
  line `( 12 ) the accumulated balance due and becoming payable to an employee participating in a`
  line `recognised provident fund, to the extent provided in rule 8 of Part A of the Fourth Schedule;`
  line `3 [( 12A ) any payment from the National Pension System Trust to an 4 [assessee] on closure of his`
  line `account or on his opting out of the pension scheme referred to in section 80CCD, to the extent it does`
  line `not exceed forty per cent. of the total amount payable to him at the time of such closure or his opting`
  line `out of the scheme;]`
  line `5 [( 12B ) any payment from the National Pension System Trust to an employee under the pension`
  line `scheme referred to in section 80CCD, on partial withdrawal made out of his account in accordance with`
  line `the terms and conditions, specified under the Pension Fund Regulatory and Development AuthorityAct,`
  line `2013 (23 of 2013) and the regulations made thereunder, to the extent it does not exceed`
  line `twenty-five per cent. of the amount of contributions made by him;]`
  line `6 [( 13 ) any payment from an approved superannuation fund made —`
  line `( i ) on the death of a beneficiary; or`
  line `( ii ) to an employee in lieu of or in commutation of an annuity on his retirement at or after a`
  line `specified age or on his becoming incapacitated prior to such retirement; or`
  line `( iii ) by way of refund of contributions on the death of a beneficiary; or`
  line `( iv ) by way of refund of contributions to an employee on his leaving the service in connection`
  line `with which the fund is established otherwise than by retirement at or after a specified age or on`
  line `his becoming incapacitated prior to such retirement, to the extent to which such payment does not`
  line `exceed the contributions made prior to the commencement of this Act and any interest`
  line `7 [thereon; or]`
  line `3 [( v ) by way of transfer to the account of the employee under a pension scheme referred to in`
  line `section 80CCD and notified by the Central Government;]`
  line `8 [( 13A ) any special allowance specifically granted to an assessee by his employer to meet`
  line `expenditure actually incurred on payment of rent (by whatever name called) in respect of residential`
  line `accommodation occupied by the assessee, to such extent 9 *** as may be prescribed having regard to`
  line `the area or place in which such accommodation is situate and other relevant considerations.]`
  line `10 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that nothing contained in this`
  line `clause shall apply in a case where —`
  line `( a ) the residential accommodation occupied by the assessee is owned by him; or`
  line `( b ) the assessee has not actually incurred expenditure on payment of rent (by whatever name`
  line `called) in respect of the residential accommodation occupied by him;]`
  line `11 [( 14 ) ( i ) any such special allowance or benefit, not being in the nature of a perquisite within the`
  line `meaning of clause ( 2 ) of section 17, specifically granted to meet expenses wholly, necessarily and`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 19 of 1968, s. 30 and the third Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-1969).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 5, for “employee” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2019).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 6 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s.7, for “thereon” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 3 (w.e.f. 6-10-1964).`
  line `9. The words “(not exceeding four hundred rupees per month” omitt ed by 23 of 1986, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `10. The Explanation inserted by Act 67 of 1984, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 6, for clause ( 14 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
