obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line 80
  line `1 [ Explanation 2. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the usance interest payable`
  line `outside India by an undertaking engaged in the business of ship-breaking in respect of purchase of a`
  line `ship from outside India shall be deemed to be the interest payable on a debt incurred in a foreign`
  line `country in respect of the purchase outside India;]`
  line `2 [( d ) by the Industrial Finance Corporation of India established by the Industrial Finance`
  line `Corporation Act, 1948 (15 of 1948), or the Industrial Development Bank of India established`
  line `under the Industrial Development Bank of India Act, 1964 (18 of 1964), 3 [or the Export-Import`
  line `Bank of India established under the Export-Import Bank of India Act, 1981 (28 of 1981),] 4 [or the`
  line `National Housing Bank established under section 3 of the National Housing Bank Act, 1987 (53`
  line `of 1987),] 5 [or the Small Industries Development Bank of India established under section 3 of the`
  line `Small Industries Development Bank of India Act, 1989 (39 of 1989),] or the Industrial Credit and`
  line `Investment Corporation of India [a company formed and registered under the Indian Companies`
  line `Act, 1913 (7 of 1913)], on 6 [any moneys borrowed by it from sources outside Indiabefore the 1st`
  line `day of June, 2001], to the extent to which such interest does not exceed the amount of interest`
  line `calculated at the rate approved by the Central Government in this behalf, having regard to the`
  line `terms of the loan and its repayment;]`
  line `( e ) by any other financial institution established in India or a banking company to which the`
  line `Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), applies (including any bank or banking institution`
  line `referred to in section 51 of that Act), on 6 [any moneys borrowed by it from sources outside India`
  line `before the 1st day of June, 2001] under a loan agreement approved by the Central Government`
  line `where the moneys are borrowed either for the purpose of advancing loans to industrial`
  line `undertakings in India for purchase outside India of raw materials or capital plant and machinery`
  line `or for the purpose of importing any goods which the Central Government may consider necessary`
  line `to import in the public interest, to the extent to which such interest does not exceed the amount of`
  line `interest calculated at the rate approved by the Central Government in this behalf, having regard to`
  line `the terms of the loan and its repayment;]`
  line `7 [( f ) by an industrial undertaking in India on any moneys borrowed by it in foreign currency`
  line `from sources outside India under 8 [a loan agreement approved by the Central Government before`
  line `the 1st day of June, 2001] having regard to the need for industrial development in India, to the`
  line `extent to which such interest does not exceed the amount of interest calculated at the rate`
  line `approved by the Central Government in this behalf, having regard to the terms of the loan and its`
  line repayment;
  line `9 [( fa ) by a scheduled bank 10 *** 11 [to a non-resident or to a person who is not ordinarily`
  line `resident within the meaning of sub-section ( 6 ) of section 6] on deposits in foreign currency where`
  line `the acceptance of such deposits by the bank is approved by the Reserve Bank of India.`
  line `12 [ Explanation. —For the purposes of this item, the expression “scheduled bank” means the State`
  line `Bank of India constituted under the State Bank of India Act, 1955 (23 of 1955), a subsidiary bank as`
  line `defined in the State Bank of India (Subsidiary Banks) Act, 1959 (38 of 1959), a corresponding new`
  line `bank constituted under section 3 of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of`
  line `Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970), or under section 3 of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and`
  line `Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1980 (40 of 1980), or any other bank being a bank included in the`
  line `Second Schedule to the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), but does not include a`
  line `co-operative bank;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 54 of 2003 s. 2, (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 26 of 1974, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
