  line `1 [( g ) by a public company formed and registered in India with the main object of carrying on`
  line `the business of providing long-term finance for construction or purchase of houses in India for`
  line `residential purposes, 2 [being a company eligible for deduction under clause ( viii ) of sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) of section 36 on any moneys borrowed by it in foreign currency from sources outside India`
  line `under 3 [a loan agreement approved by the Central Government before the 1st day of June, 2003],`
  line `to the extent to which such interest does not exceed the amount of interest calculated at the rate`
  line `approved by the Central Government in this behalf, having regard to the terms of the loan and its`
  line repayment.]
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of 4 [items ( f ), ( fa ) and ( g )], the expression “foreign currency”`
  line `shall have the meaning assigned to it in the 5 [Foreign Exchange Management Act, 1999`
  line `(42 of 1999)];]`
  line `6 [( h ) by any public sector company in respect of such bonds or debentures and subject to such`
  line `conditions, including the condition that the holder of such bonds or debentures registers his name`
  line `and the holding with that company, as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, specify in this behalf;]`
  line `7 [( i ) by Government on deposits made by an employee of the Central Government or a State`
  line `Government 8 [or a public sector company], in accordance with such scheme as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, frame in this behalf, out of the moneys`
  line `due to him on account of his retirement, whether on superannuation or otherwise.]`
  line `9 [ 10 [ Explanation 1]. — For the purposes of this sub- clause, the expression “industrial undertaking”`
  line `means any undertaking which is engaged in —`
  line `( a ) the manufacture or processing of goods; or`
  line `11 [( aa ) the manufacture of computer software or recording of programme on any disc, tape,`
  line `perforated media or other information device; or]`
  line `( b ) the business of generation or distribution of electricity or any other form of power; or`
  line `12 [( ba ) the business of providing telecommunication services; or]`
  line `( c ) mining; or`
  line `( d ) the construction of ships; or`
  line `13 [( da ) the business of ship-breaking; or]`
  line `14 [( e ) the operation of ships or aircrafts or construction or operation of rail systems.]]`
  line `15 [ Explanation 1A. — For the purposes of this sub- clause, the expression “interest” shall not`
  line `include interest paid on delayed payment of loan or on default if it is in excess of two per cent.`
  line `per annum over the rate of interest payable in terms of such loan.]`
  line `16 [ Explanation 2. — For the purposes of this clause, the expression “interest” includes hedging`
  line `transaction charges on account of currency fluctuation;]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1983, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1983).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 5, for “being a company approved by the Central Government for the purposes of clause ( viii )`
  line `of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 36” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2000).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 6, for “a loan agreement approved by the Central Government” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2004).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 5 for “items ( f ) and ( g )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1991).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 4, for “the Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 13 of 1989, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `10. Explanation renumbered as Explanation 1 thereof by the Act 27 of 1999, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `11. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `12. Ins. by 26 of 1997, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `13. Ins. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
