  line `1 [( v ) interest on —`
  line `( a ) securities held by the Welfare Commissioner, Bhopal Gas Victims, Bhopal, in the`
  line `Reserve Bank's SGL Account No. SL/DH 048;`
  line `( b ) deposits for the benefit of the victims of the Bhopal gas leak disaster held in such`
  line `account, with the Reserve Bank of India or with a public sector bank, as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify, whether prospectively or retrospectively but`
  line `in no case earlier than the 1st day of April, 1994 in this behalf.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- clause, the expression “public sector bank” shall have`
  line `the meaning assigned to it in the Explanation to clause ( 23D );]`
  line `2 [( vi ) interest on Gold Deposit Bonds issued under the Gold Deposit Scheme, 1999 3 [ or deposit`
  line `certificates issued under the Gold Monetisation Scheme, 2015] notified by the Central Government;`
  line `4 [( vii ) interest on bonds —`
  line `( a ) issued by a local authority or by a State Pooled Finance Entity; and`
  line `( b ) specified by the Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- clause, the expression “State Pooled Finance Entity”`
  line `shall mean such entity which is set up in accordance with the guidelines for the Pooled Finance`
  line `Development Scheme notified by the Central Government in the Ministry of Urban Development;]`
  line `5 [( viii ) any income by way of interest received by a non-resident or a person who is not ordinarily`
  line `resident, in India on a deposit made on or after the 1st day of April, 2005, in an Offshore Banking`
  line `Unit referred to in clause ( u ) of section 2 of the Special Economic Zones Act, 2005 (28 of 2005);]`
  line `6 [( 15A ) any payment made, by an Indian company engaged in the business of operation of`
  line `aircraft, to acquire an aircraft or an aircraft engine (other than a payment for providing spares,`
  line `facilities or services in connection with the operation of leased aircraft) on lease from the`
  line `Government of a foreign State or a foreign enterprise under an agreement 7 [ 8 [, not being an`
  line `agreement entered into between the 1st day of April, 1997 and the 31st day of March, 1999,] and]`
  line `approved by the Central Government in this behalf:`
  line `9 [Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall apply to any such agreement entered into on`
  line `or after the 10 [1st day of April, [2007].]`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, the expression “foreign enterprise” means a person`
  line `who is a non-resident;]`
  line `( 16 ) scholarships granted to meet the cost of education;`
  line `11 [( 17 ) any income by way of —`
  line `( i ) daily allowance received by any person by reason of his membership of Parliament or of`
  line `any State Legislature or of any Committee thereof; 12 ***`
  line `13 [( ii ) any allowance received by any person by reason of his membership of Parliament`
  line `under the Members of Parliament (Constituency Allowance) Rules, 1986;`
  line `14 [( iii ) any constituency allowance received by any person by reason of his membership of any`
  line `State Legislature under any Act or rules made by that State Legislature;]]]`
