  line 83
  line `1 [( 17A ) any payment made, whether in cash or in kind, —`
  line `( i ) in pursuance of any award instituted in the public interest by the Central Government or`
  line `any State Government or instituted by any other body and approved by the Central Government`
  line `in this behalf; or`
  line `( ii ) as a reward by the Central Government or any State Government for such purposes as`
  line `may be approved by the Central Government in this behalf in the public interest;]`
  line `2 [( 18 ) any income by way of —`
  line `( i ) pension received by an individual who has been in the service of the Central Government`
  line `or State Government and has been awarded “Param Vir Chakra” or “Maha Vir Chakra” or “Vir`
  line `Chakra” or such other gallantry award as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, specify in this behalf;`
  line `( ii ) family pension received by any member of the family of an individual referred to in`
  line `sub-clause ( i ).`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, the expression “family” shall have the meaning`
  line `assigned to it in the Explanation to clause ( 5 );]`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 [( 19 ) family pension received by the widow or children or nominated heirs, as the case may be,`
  line `of a member of the armed forces (including para-military forces) of the Union, where the death of`
  line `such member has occurred in the course of operational duties, in such circumstances and subject to`
  line `such conditions, as may be prescribed;]`
  line `5 [( 19A ) the annual value of any one palace in the occupation of a Ruler, being a palace, the annual`
  line `value whereof was exempt from income-tax before the commencement of the Constitution`
  line `(Twenty-sixth Amendment) Act, 1971, by virtue of the provisions of the Merged States (Taxation`
  line `Concessions) Order, 1949, or the Part B States (Taxation Concessions) Order, 1950, or, as the case`
  line `may be, the Jammu and Kashmir (Taxation Concessions) Order, 1958:`
  line `Provided that for the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1972, the annual value`
  line `of every such palace in the occupation of such Ruler during the relevant previous year shall be`
  line `exempt from income-tax;]`
  line `( 20 ) the income of a local authority which is chargeable under the head 6 *** “Income from house`
  line `property”, “Capital gains” or “Income from other sources” or from a trade or business carried on by it`
  line `7 [which accrues or arises from the supply of a commodity or service (not being water or electricity)`
  line `within its own jurisdictional area or from the supply of water or electricity within or outside its own`
  line `jurisdictional area].`
  line `8 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, the expression “local authority” means—`
  line `( i ) Panchayat as referred to in clause ( d ) of article 243 of the Constitution; or`
  line `( ii ) Municipality as referred to in clause ( e ) of article 243P of the Constitution; or`
  line `( iii ) Municipal Committee and District Board,`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 6, for clauses ( 17A ), ( 17B ) and ( 18 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `3. Clause ( 18A ) omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 54 of 1972, s. 7 (w.e.f. 28-12-1971).`
  line `6. The words “Interest on securities” omitted by Act 26 of 1988, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 32 of 1971, s. 4, for “which accrues or arises from the supply of a commodity or service within its own`
  line `jurisdictional area” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1972).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
