obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line 86
  line `1 [( 23A ) any income (other than income chargeable under the head 2 ***“Income from house`
  line `property” or any income received for rendering any specific services or income by way of interest or`
  line `dividends derived from its investments) of an association or institution established in India having as`
  line `its object the control, supervision, regulation or encouragement of the profession of law, medicine,`
  line `accountancy, engineering or architecture or such other profession as the Central Government may`
  line `specify in this behalf, from time to time, by notification in the Official Gazette:`
  line `Provided that —`
  line `( i ) the association or institution applies its income, or accumulates it for application, solely`
  line `to the objects for which it is established; and`
  line `( ii ) the association or institution is for the time being approved for the purpose of this clause`
  line `by the Central Government by general or special order:]`
  line `3 [Provided further that where the association or institution has been approved by the Central`
  line `Government and subsequently that Government is satisfied that —`
  line `( i ) such association or institution has not applied or accumulated its income in accordance`
  line `with the provisions contained in the first proviso; or`
  line `( ii ) the activities of the association or institution are not being carried out in accordance with`
  line `all or any of the conditions subject to which such association or institution was approved,`
  line `it may, at any time after giving a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the proposed`
  line `withdrawal to the concerned association or institution, by order, withdraw the approval and forward a`
  line `copy of the order withdrawing the approval to such association or institution and to the Assessing`
  line Officer;]
  line `4 [( 23AA ) any income received by any person on behalf of any Regimental Fund or Non-Public`
  line `Fund established by the armed forces of the Union for the welfare of the past and present members of`
  line `such forces or their dependants;]`
  line `5 [( 23AAA ) any income received by any person on behalf of a fund established, for such purposes`
  line `as may be notified by the Board in the Official Gazette, for the welfare of employees or their`
  line `dependants and of which fund such employees are members if such fund fulfils the following`
  line `conditions, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the fund —`
  line `( i ) applies its income or accumulates it for application, wholly and exclusively to the`
  line `objects for which it is established; and`
  line `( ii ) invests its funds and contributions and other sums received by it in the forms or`
  line `modes specified in sub-section ( 5 ) of section 11;`
  line `( b ) the fund is approved by the 6 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] in accordance`
  line `with the rules made in this behalf:`
  line `Provided that any such approval shall at any one time have effect for such assessment year or`
  line `years not exceeding three assessment years as may be specified in the order of approval;]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 1965, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `2. The words “Interest on securities” or’ omitted by Act 26 of 1988, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1996).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-87
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Page 87`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  sourcePage 87
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line 87
  line `1 [( 23AAB ) any income of a fund, by whatever name called, set up by the Life Insurance`
  line `Corporation of India on or after the 1st day of August, 1996 2 [or any other insurer under a pension`
  line `scheme], —`
  line `( i ) to which contribution is made by any person for the purpose of receiving pension from`
  line `such fund;`
  line `( ii ) which is approved by the Controller of Insurance 3 [or the Insurance Regulatory and`
  line `Development Authority established under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 3 of the Insurance`
  line `Regulatory and Development Authority Act, 1999 (41 of 1999), as the case may be].`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, the expression “Controller of Insurance” shall`
  line `have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( 5B ) of section 2 of the Insurance Act, 1938`
  line `(4 of 1938);]`
  line `4 [( 23B ) any income of an institution constituted as a public charitable trust or registered under`
  line `the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860), or under any law corresponding to that Act in force`
  line `in any part of India, and existing solely for the development of khadi or village industries or both, and`
  line `not for purposes of profit, to the extent such income is attributable to the business of production, sale,`
  line `or marketing, of khadi or products of village industries:`
  line `Provided that —`
  line `( i ) the institution applies its income, or accumulates it for application, solely for the`
  line `development of khadi or village industries or both; and`
  line `( ii ) the institution is, for the time being, approved for the purpose of this clause by the Khadi`
  line `and Village Industries Commission:`
  line `Provided further that the Commission shall not, at any one time, grant such approval for more`
  line `than three assessment years beginning with the assessment year next following the financial year in`
  line `which it is granted:`
  line `5 [Provided also that where the institution has been approved by the Khadi and Village Industries`
  line `Commission and subsequently that Commission is satisfied that —`
  line `( i ) the institution has not applied or accumulated its income in accordance with the provisions`
  line `contained in the first proviso; or`
  line `( ii ) the activities of the institution are not being carried out in accordance with all or any of`
  line `the conditions subject to which such institution was approved,`
  line `it may, at any time after giving a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the proposed`
  line `withdrawal to the concerned institution, by order, withdraw the approval and forward a copy of the`
  line `order withdrawing the approval to such institution and to the Assessing Officer.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( i ) “Khadi and Village Industries Commission” means the Kha di and Village`
  line `Industries Commission established under the Khadi and Village Industries Commission`
  line `Act, 1956 (61 of 1956);`
  line `( ii ) “khadi” and “village industries” have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that`
  line Act;]
  line `6 [( 23BB ) any income of an authority (whether known as the Khadi and Village Industries Board`
  line `or by any other name) established in a State by or under a State or Provincial Act for the development`
  line `of khadi or village industries in the State.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1997).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 5, for “under a pension scheme” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2002).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 1974, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-6-1974).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 21 of 1979, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
