  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  sourcePage 88
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line 88
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, “khadi” and “village industries” have the`
  line `meanings respectively assigned to them in the Khadi and Village Industries Commission Act, 1956`
  line `(61 of 1956);`
  line `( 23BBA ) any income of any body or authority (whether or not a body corporate or corporation`
  line `sole) established, constituted or appointed by or under any Central, State or Provincial Act which`
  line `provides for the administration of any one or more of the following, that is to say, public religious or`
  line `charitable trusts or endowments (including maths, temples, gurdwaras, wakfs, churches, synagogues,`
  line `agiaries or other places of public religious worship) or societies for religious or charitable purposes`
  line `registered as such under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860), or any other law for the`
  line `time being in force:`
  line `Provided that nothing in this clause shall be construed to exempt from tax the income of any trust,`
  line `endowment or society referred to therein;]`
  line `1 [( 23BBB ) any income of the European Economic Community derived in India by way of`
  line `interest, dividends or capital gains from investments made out of its funds under such scheme as the`
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, “European Economic Community” means the`
  line `European Economic Community established by the Treaty of Rome of 25th March, 1957;]`
  line `2 [( 23BBC ) any income of the SAARC Fund for Regional Projects set up by Colombo Declaration`
  line `issued on the 21st day of December, 1991 by the Heads of State or Government of the Member`
  line `Countries of South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation established on the 8th day of`
  line `December, 1985 by the Charter of the South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation;]`
  line `3 [( 23BBD ) any income of the Secretariat of the Asian Organisation of the Supreme`
  line `Audit Institutions registered as “ASOSAI - SECRETARIAT” under the Societies Registration`
  line `Act, 1860 (21 of 1860) for 4 [ten previous years relevant to the assessment years beginning on the`
  line `1st day of April, 2001 and ending on the 31st day of March, 2011];`
  line `( 23BBE ) any income of the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority established under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 3 of the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority Act, 1999`
  line `(41 of 1999);]`
  line `5 [( 23BBF ) any income of the North-Eastern Development Finance Corporation Limited, being a`
  line `company formed and registered under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956):`
  line `Provided that in computing the total income of the North-Eastern Development Finance`
  line `Corporation Limited, the amount to the extent of —`
  line `( i ) twenty per cent. of the total income for assessment year beginning on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2006;`
  line `( ii ) forty per cent. of the total income for assessment year beginning on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2007;`
  line `( iii ) sixty per cent. of the total income for assessment year beginning on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2008;`
  line `( iv ) eighty per cent. of the total income for assessment year beginning on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2009;`
  line `( v ) one hundred per cent. of the total income for assessment year beginning on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2010 and any subsequent assessment year or years,`
  line `shall be included in such total income;]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 38 of 1993, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1994).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 6, for certain words, figures and letters (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
