  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  sourcePage 89
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line 89
  line `1 [( 23BBG ) any income of the Central Electricity Regulatory Commission constituted under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 76 of the Electricity Act, 2003 (36 of 2003);]`
  line `2 [( 23BBH ) any income of the Prasar Bharati (Broadcasting Corporation of India) established`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 3 of the Prasar Bharati (Broadcasting Corporation of India) Act, 1990`
  line `(25 of 1990);]`
  line `3 [( 23C ) any income received by any person on behalf of —`
  line `( i ) the Prime Minister's National Relief Fund; or`
  line `( ii ) the Prime Minister's Fund (Promotion of Folk Art); or`
  line `( iii ) the Prime Minister's Aid to Students Fund; or`
  line `4 [( iiia ) the National Foundation for Communal Harmony; or]`
  line `5 [( iiiaa ) the Swachh Bharat Kosh, set up by the Central Government; or`
  line `( iiiaaa ) the Clean Ganga Fund, set up by the Central Government; or]`
  line `6 [( iiiaaaa ) the Chief Minister’s Relief Fund or the Lieutenant Governor’s Relie f Fund in`
  line `respect of any State or Union territory as referred to in sub-clause ( iiihf ) of clause ( a ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 80G; or`
  line `7 [( iiiab ) any university or other educational institution existing solely for educational`
  line `purposes and not for purposes of profit, and which is wholly or substantially financed by the`
  line `Government; or`
  line `( iiiac ) any hospital or other institution for the reception and treatment of persons suffering`
  line `from illness or mental defectiveness or for the reception and treatment of persons during`
  line `convalescence or of persons requiring medical attention or rehabilitation, existing solely for`
  line `philanthropic purposes and not for purposes of profit, and which is wholly or substantially`
  line `financed by the Government.`
  line `8 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of sub-clauses ( iiiab ) and ( iiiac ), any university or other`
  line `educational institution, hospital or other institution referred therein, shall be considered as being`
  line `substantially financed by the Government for any previous year, if the Government grant to such`
  line `university or other educational institution, hospital or other institution exceeds such percentage of`
  line `the total receipts including any voluntary contributions, as may be prescribed, of such university`
  line `or other educational institution, hospital or other institution, as the case may be, during the`
  line `relevant previous year;] or`
  line `( iiiad ) any university or other educational institution existing solely for educational purposes`
  line `and not for purposes of profit if the aggregate annual receipts of such university or educational`
  line `institution do not exceed the amount of annual receipts as may be prescribed; or`
  line `( iiiae ) any hospital or other institution for the reception and treatment of persons suffering`
  line `from illness or mental defectiveness or for the reception and treatment of persons during`
  line `convalescence or of persons requiring medical attention or rehabilitation, existing solely for`
  line `philanthropic purposes and not for purposes of profit, if the aggregate annual receipts of such`
  line `hospital or institution do not exceed the amount of annual receipts as may be prescribed; or]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 38 of 1993, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
