obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line 95
  line `1 [( 23DA ) any income of a securitisation trust from the activity of securitisation.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( a ) “securitisation” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it, —`
  line `( i ) in clause ( r ) of sub-regulation ( 1 ) of regulation 2 of the Securities and Exchange`
  line `Board of India (Public Offer and Listing of Securitised Debt Instruments) Regulations, 2008`
  line `made under the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992) and the`
  line `Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956); or`
  line `2 [( ia ) in clause ( z ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 2 of the Securitisation and Reconstruction`
  line `of Financial Assets and Enforcement of Security Interest Act, 2002 (54 of 2002); or]`
  line `( ii ) under the guidelines on securitisation of standard assets issued by the Reserve Bank`
  line `of India;`
  line `( b ) “securitisation trust” shall have the meaning assigned to it in`
  line `the Explanation below 3 [section 115TCA];]`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `5 [( 23EA ) 6 [any income, by way of contributions received from recognised stock exchanges and`
  line `the members thereof,] of such Investor Protection Fund set up by recognised stock exchanges in`
  line `India, either jointly or separately, as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify in this behalf:`
  line `Provided that where any amount standing to the credit of the Fund and not charged to income-tax`
  line `during any previous year is shared, either wholly or in part, with a recognised stock exchange, the`
  line `whole of the amount so shared shall be deemed to be the income of the previous year in which such`
  line `amount is so shared and shall accordingly be chargeable to income-tax;]`
  line `7 [( 23EB ) any income of the 8 [Credit Guarantee Fund Trust for Small Industries], being a trust`
  line `created by the Government of India and the Small Industries Development Bank of India established`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 3 of the Small Industries Development Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1989 (39 of 1989), for five previous years relevant to the assessment years beginning on the`
  line `1st day of April, 2002 and ending on the 31st day of March, 2007;]`
  line `9 [( 23EC ) any income, by way of contributions received from commodity exchanges and the`
  line `members thereof, of such Investor Protection Fund set up by commodity exchanges in India, either`
  line `jointly or separately, as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify`
  line `in this behalf:`
  line `Provided that where any amount standing to the credit of the said Fund and not charged to`
  line `income-tax during any previous year is shared, either wholly or in part, with a commodity exchange,`
  line `the whole of the amount so shared shall be deemed to be the income of the previous year in which`
  line `such amount is so shared and shall accordingly be chargeable to income-tax.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for “section 115TC” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `4. Clause ( 23E ) omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 4, for “any income” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2007).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 6, for “Credit Guarantee Fund Trust for Small Scale Industries” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2002).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
