  title `Page 96`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  sourcePage 96
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line 96
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, “commodity exchange” shall mean a “ registered`
  line `association ” as defined in clause ( jj ) of section 2 of the Forward Contracts (Regulation)`
  line `Act, 1952 (74 of 1952);]`
  line `1 [( 23ED ) any income, by way of contributions received from a depository, of such Investor`
  line `Protection Fund set up in accordance with the regulations by a depository as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf:`
  line `Provided that where any amount standing to the credit of the Fund and not charged to income-tax`
  line `during any previous year is shared, either wholly or in part with a depository, the whole of the amount`
  line `so shared shall be deemed to be the income of the previous year in which such amount is so shared`
  line `and shall, accordingly, be chargeable to income-tax.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( i ) “ depository ” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause ( e ) of sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 2 of the Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996);`
  line `( ii ) “ regulations ” means the regulations made under the Securities and Exchange Board of`
  line `India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992) and the Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996);]`
  line `2 [( 23EE ) any specified income of such Core Settlement Guarantee Fund, set up by a recognised`
  line `clearing corporation in accordance with the regulations, as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf:`
  line `Provided that where any amount standing to the credit of the Fund and not charged to income-tax`
  line `during any previous year is shared, either wholly or in part with the specified person, the whole of the`
  line `amount so shared shall be deemed to be the income of the previous year in which such amount is so`
  line `shared and shall, accordingly, be chargeable to income-tax.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( i ) “recognised clearing corporation” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in`
  line `clause ( o ) of sub-regulation ( 1 ) of regulation 2 of the Securities Contracts (Regulation) (Stock`
  line `Exchanges and Clearing Corporations) Regulations, 2012 made under the Securities and`
  line `Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992) and the Securities Contracts (Regulation)`
  line `Act, 1956 (42 of 1956);`
  line `( ii ) “regulations” means the Securities Contracts (Regulation) (Stock Exchanges and Clearing`
  line `Corporations) Regulations, 2012 made under the Securities and Exchange Board of India`
  line `Act, 1992 (15 of 1992) and the Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956);`
  line `( iii ) “specified income” shall mean,—`
  line `( a ) the income by way of contribution received from specified persons;`
  line `( b ) the income by way of penalties imposed by the recognised clearing corporation and`
  line `credited to the Core Settlement Guarantee Fund; or`
  line `( c ) the income from investment made by the Fund;`
  line `( iv ) “specified person” shall mean,—`
  line `( a ) any recognised clearing corporation which establishes and maintains the Core`
  line `Settlement Guarantee Fund;`
  line `( b ) any recognised stock exchange, being a shareholder in such recognised clearing`
  line `corporation, or a contributor to the Core Settlement Guarantee Fund; and`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
