  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-98
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Page 98`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  sourcePage 98
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line 98
  line `Provided further that any approval by the Central Government shall, at any one time, have effect`
  line `for such assessment year or years, not exceeding three assessment years, as may be specified in the`
  line `order of approval:`
  line `1 [Provided also that nothing contained in this clause shall apply in respect of any investment`
  line `made after the 31st day of March, 2000.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( a ) “venture capital fund” means such fund, operating under a trust deed registered under the`
  line `provisions of the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), established to raise monies by the trustees`
  line `for investments mainly by way of acquiring equity shares of a venture capital undertaking in`
  line `accordance with the prescribed guidelines;`
  line `( b ) “venture capital company” means such company as has made investments by way of`
  line `acquiring equity shares of venture capital undertakings in accordance with the prescribed`
  line `guidelines; and`
  line `( c ) “venture capital undertaking” means such domestic company whose shares are not listed`
  line `in a recognised stock exchange in India and which is engaged in the —`
  line `( i ) business of —`
  line `( A ) software;`
  line `( B ) information technology;`
  line `( C ) production of basic drugs in the pharmaceutical sector;`
  line `( D ) bio-technology;`
  line `( E ) agriculture and allied sectors; or`
  line `( F ) such other sectors as may be notified by the Central Government in this behalf; or`
  line `( ii ) production or manufacture of any article or substance for which patent has been`
  line `granted to the National Research Laboratory or any other scientific research institution`
  line `approved by the Department of Science and Technology;]`
  line `1 [( 23FB ) any income of a venture capital company or venture capital fund 2 [from investment] in a`
  line `venture capital undertaking:`
  line `3 [Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall apply in respect of any income of a venture`
  line `capital company or venture capital fund, being an investment fund specified in clause ( a ) of`
  line `the Explanation 1 to section 115UB, of the previous year relevant to the assessment year beginning`
  line `on or after the 1st day of April, 2016.]`
  line `4 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( a ) “venture capital company” means a company which—`
  line `( A ) has been granted a certificate of registration, before the 21st day of May, 2012, as a`
  line `Venture Capital Fund and is regulated under the Securities and Exchange Board of India`
  line `(Venture Capital Funds) Regulations, 1996 (hereinafter referred to as the Venture Capital`
  line `Funds Regulations) made under the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of`
  line `1992); or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 6, for “set up to raise funds for investment” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2008).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 5 for the Explanation 1 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-99
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Page 99`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  sourcePage 99
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line 99
  line `( B ) has been granted a certificate of registration as Venture Capital Fund as a sub-`
  line `category of Category I Alternative Investment Fund and is regulated under the Securities and`
  line `Exchange Board of India (Alternative Investment Funds) Regulations, 2012 (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as the Alternative Investment Funds Regulations) made under the Securities and`
  line `Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992), and which fulfils the following conditions,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( i ) it is not listed on a recognised stock exchange;`
  line `( ii ) it has invested not less than two-thirds of its investible funds in unlisted equity`
  line `shares or equity linked instruments of venture capital undertaking; and`
  line `( iii ) it has not invested in any venture capital undertaking in which its director or a`
  line `substantial shareholder (being a beneficial owner of equity shares exceeding ten per cent.`
  line `of its equity share capital) holds, either individually or collectively, equity shares in`
  line `excess of fifteen per cent. of the paid-up equity share capital of such venture capital`
  line undertaking;
  line `( b ) “venture capital fund” means a fund—`
  line `( A ) operating under a trust deed registered under the provisions of the Registration`
  line `Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), which —`
  line `( I ) has been granted a certificate of registration, before the 21st day of May, 2012, as`
  line `a Venture Capital Fund and is regulated under the Venture Capital Funds Regulations; or`
  line `( II ) has been granted a certificate of registration as Venture Capital Fund as a sub-`
  line `category of Category I Alternative Investment Fund under the Alternative Investment`
  line `Funds Regulations and which fulfils the following conditions, namely: —`
  line `( i ) it has invested not less than two-thirds of its investible funds in unlisted equity`
  line `shares or equity linked instruments of venture capital undertaking;`
  line `( ii ) it has not invested in any venture capital undertaking in which its trustee or`
  line `the settler holds, either individually or collectively, equity shares in excess of fifteen`
  line `per cent. of the paid-up equity share capital of such venture capital undertaking; and`
  line `( iii ) the units, if any, issued by it are not listed in any recognised stock`
  line `exchange; or`
  line `( B ) operating as a venture capital scheme made by the Unit Trust of India established`
  line `under the Unit Trust of India Act, 1963 (52 of 1963);`
  line `( c ) “ venture capital undertaking ” means —`
  line `( i ) a venture capital undertaking as defined in clause ( n ) of regulation 2 of the Venture`
  line `Capital Funds Regulations; or`
  line `( ii ) a venture capital undertaking as defined in clause ( aa ) of sub-regulation ( 1 ) of`
  line `regulation 2 of the Alternative Investment Funds Regulations;]]`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `1. The Explanation 2 omitted by Act 23 of 2004, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-10-2004).`
