  line 101
  line `( 25 ) ( i ) interest on securities which are held by, or are the property of, any provident fund to`
  line `which the Provident Funds Act, 1925 (19 of 1925), applies, and any capital gains of the fund arising`
  line `from the sale, exchange or transfer of such securities;`
  line `( ii ) any income received by the trustees on behalf of a recognised provident fund;`
  line `( iii ) any income received by the trustees on behalf of an approved superannuation fund;`
  line `1 [( iv ) any income received by the trustees on behalf of an approved gratuity fund;]`
  line `2 [( v ) any income received —`
  line `( a ) by the Board of Trustees constituted under the Coal Mines Provident Funds and`
  line `Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1948 (46 of 1948), on behalf of the Deposit-linked Insurance Fund`
  line `established under section 3G of that Act; or`
  line `( b ) by the Board of Trustees constituted under the Employees' Provident Funds and`
  line `Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1952 (19 of 1952), on behalf of the Deposit-linked Insurance Fund`
  line `established under section 6C of that Act;]`
  line `3 [( 25A ) any income of the Employees’ State Insurance Fund set up under the provisions of the`
  line `Employees' State Insurance Act, 1948 (34 of 1948);]`
  line `4 [( 26 ) in the case of a member of a Scheduled Tribe as defined in clause ( 25 ) of article 366 of the`
  line `Constitution, residing in any area specified in Part I or Part II of the Table appended to paragraph 20`
  line `of the Sixth Schedule to the Constitution or in the 5 [States of Arunachal Pradesh, Manipur, Mizoram,`
  line `Nagaland and Tripura] or in the areas covered by notification No. TAD/R/35/50/109, dated the 23rd`
  line `February, 1951, issued by the Governor of Assam under the proviso to sub-paragraph ( 3 ) of the said`
  line `paragraph 20 [as it stood immediately before the commencement of the North-Eastern Areas`
  line `(Reorganisation) Act, 1971 (81 of 1971)] 6 [or in the Ladakh region of the State of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir], any income which accrues or arises to him, —`
  line `( a ) from any source in the areas 7 [or States aforesaid], or`
  line `( b ) by way of dividend or interest on securities;]`
  line `8 [( 26A ) any income accruing or arising to any person 9 *** from any source in the district of`
  line `Ladakh or outside India in any previous year relevant to any assessment year commencing before the`
  line `10 [1st day of April, 1989], where such person is resident in the said district in that previous year:`
  line `Provided that this clause shall not apply in the case of any such person unless he was resident in`
  line `that district in the previous year relevant to the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April,`
  line 1962.
  line `1. Ins. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 99 of 1976, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `4. Subs. by the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1974, for clause 26`
  line `(w.e.f. 21-1-1972).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 6, for “States of Nagaland, Manipur and Tripura or in the Union territories of Arunachal`
  line `Pradesh and Mizoram” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1995).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 6, for “States or Union territories aforesaid” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1995).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 15 of 1965, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `9. The brackets and words “(not being an individual who is in the service of Government)” omitted by Act 32 of 1971, s. 4`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 32 of 1985, s. 4, for “1st day of April, 1986” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1985).`
