obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line 102
  line `1 [ Explanation 1]. — For the purposes of this clause, a person shall be deemed to be resident in the`
  line `district of Ladakh if he fulfils the requirements of sub-section ( 1 )or sub-section ( 2 ) or`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 4 ) of section 6, as the case may be, subject to the modifications that —`
  line `( i ) references in those sub-sections to India shall be construed as references to the said`
  line `district; and`
  line `( ii ) in clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 3 ), reference to Indian company shall be construed as`
  line `reference to a company formed and registered under any law for the time being in force in the`
  line `State of Jammu and Kashmir and having its registered office in that district in that year.]`
  line `2 [ Explanation 2. — In this clause, references to the district of Ladakh shall be construed as`
  line `references to the areas comprised in the said district on the 30th day of June, 1979;]`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 [( 26AAA ) in case of an individual, being a Sikkimese, any income which accrues or arises to`
  line `him —`
  line `( a ) from any source in the State of Sikkim; or`
  line `( b ) by way of dividend or interest on securities:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall apply to a Sikkimese woman who, on or`
  line `after the 1st day of April, 2008, marries an individual who is not a Sikkimese.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, “Sikkimese” shall mean—`
  line `( i ) an individual, whose name is recorded in the register maintained under the Sikkim`
  line `Subjects Regulation, 1961 read with the Sikkim Subject Rules, 1961 (hereinafter referred to as`
  line `the “Register of Sikkim Subjects”), immediately before the 26th day of April, 1975; or`
  line `( ii ) an individual, whose name is included in the Register of Sikkim Subjects by virtue of the`
  line `Government of India Order No. 26030/36/90-I.C.I., dated the 7th August, 1990 and Order of even`
  line `number dated the 8th April, 1991; or`
  line `( iii ) any other individual, whose name does not appear in the Register of Sikkim Subjects, but`
  line `it is established beyond doubt that the name of such individual’s father or husband or paternal`
  line `grand-father or brother from the same father has been recorded in that register;]`
  line `5 [( 26AAB ) any income of an agricultural produce market committee or board constituted under`
  line `any law for the time being in force for the purpose of regulating the marketing of agricultural`
  line produce;]
  line `6 [( 26B ) any income of a corporation established by a Central, State or Provincial Act or of any`
  line `other body, institution or association (being a body, institution or association wholly financed by`
  line `Government) where such corporation or other body or institution or association has been established`
  line `or formed for promoting the interests of the 7 [members of the Scheduled Castes or the Scheduled`
  line `Tribes or backward classes or of any two or all of them].`
  line `1. The Explanation renumbered as Explanation 1 by Act 11 of 1983, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1980).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1980).`
  line `3. Clause ( 26AA ) omitted by Act 26 of 1997, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 13 of 1980, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 6, for “members of either the Scheduled Castes or the Scheduled Tribes or of both”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
