obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line 103
  line `1 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( a ) “Scheduled Castes” and “Scheduled Tribes” shall have the meanings respectively assigned to`
  line `them in clauses ( 24 ) and ( 25 ) of article 366 of the Constitution;`
  line `( b ) “backward classes” means such classes of citizens, other than the Scheduled Castes and the`
  line `Scheduled Tribes, as may be notified —`
  line `( i ) by the Central Government; or`
  line `( ii ) by any State Government,`
  line `as the case may be, from time to time;]]`
  line `2 [( 26BB ) any income of a corporation established by the Central Government or any State`
  line `Government for promoting the interests of the members of a minority community.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, “minority community” means a community`
  line `notified as such by the Central Government in the Official Gazette in this behalf;]`
  line `3 [( 26BBB ) any income of a corporation established by a Central, State or Provincial Act for the`
  line `welfare and economic upliftment of ex-servicemen being the citizens of India.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, “ex - serviceman” means a person who has served`
  line `in any rank, whether as combatant or non-combatant, in the armed forces of the Union or armed`
  line `forces of the Indian States before the commencement of the Constitution (but excluding the Assam`
  line `Rifles, Defence Security Corps, General Reserve Engineering Force, Lok Sahayak Sena, Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir Militia and Territorial Army) for a continuous period of not less than six months after`
  line `attestation and has been released, otherwise than by way of dismissal or discharge on account of`
  line `misconduct or inefficiency, and in the case of a deceased or incapacitated ex-serviceman includes his`
  line `wife, children, father, mother, minor brother, widowed daughter and widowed sister, wholly`
  line `dependant upon such ex-serviceman immediately before his death or incapacitation;]`
  line `4 [( 27 ) any income of a co-operative society formed for promoting the interests of the members of`
  line `either the Scheduled Castes or Scheduled Tribes or both referred to in clause ( 26B ):`
  line `Provided that the membership of the co-operative society consists of only other co-operative`
  line `societies formed for similar purposes and the finances of the society are provided by the Government`
  line `and such other societies;]`
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `6 * * * * *`
  line `7 [( 29A ) any income accruing or arising to —`
  line `( a ) the Coffee Board constituted under section 4 of the Coffee Act, 1942 (7 of 1942) in any`
  line `previous year relevant to any assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 1962`
  line `or the previous year in which such Board was constituted, whichever is later;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 6, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Clause ( 28 ) omitted by Act 26 of 1997, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `6. Clause ( 29 ) omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 6 (w.e.f. 11-5-1999).`
