obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line 104
  line `( b ) the Rubber Board constituted under sub-section (1) of section 4 of the Rubber Board`
  line `Act, 1947 (24 of 1947) in any previous year relevant to any assessment year commencing on or`
  line `after the 1st day of April, 1962 or the previous year in which such Board was constituted,`
  line `whichever is later;`
  line `( c ) the Tea Board established under section 4 of the Tea Act, 1953 (29 of 1953) in any`
  line `previous year relevant to any assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 1962`
  line `or the previous year in which such Board was constituted, whichever is later;`
  line `( d ) the Tobacco Board constituted under the Tobacco Board Act, 1975 (4 of 1975) in any`
  line `previous year relevant to any assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 1975`
  line `or the previous year in which such Board was constituted, whichever is later;`
  line `( e ) the Marine Products Export Development Authority established under section 4 of the`
  line `Marine Products Export Development Authority Act, 1972 (13 of 1972) in any previous year`
  line `relevant to any assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 1972 or the previous`
  line `year in which such Authority was constituted, whichever is later;`
  line `( f ) the Agricultural and Processed Food Products Export Development Authority established`
  line `under section 4 of the Agricultural and Processed Food Products Export Development Act, 1985`
  line `(2 of 1986) in any previous year relevant to any assessment year commencing on or after the 1st`
  line `day of April, 1985 or the previous year in which such Authority was constituted, whichever is`
  line later;
  line `( g ) the Spices Board constituted under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 3 of the Spices Board Act,`
  line `1986 (10 of 1986) in any previous year relevant to any assessment year commencing on or after`
  line `the 1st day of April, 1986 or the previous year in which such Board was constituted, whichever is`
  line later;]
  line `1 [( h ) the Coir Board established under section 4 of the Coir Industry Act, 1953 (45 of 1953);]`
  line `2 [( 30 ) in the case of an assessee who carries on the business of growing and manufacturing tea in`
  line `India, the amount of any subsidy received from or through the Tea Board under any such scheme for`
  line `replantation or replacement of tea bushes 3 [or for rejuvenation or consolidation of areas used for`
  line `cultivation of tea] as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify:`
  line `Provided that the assessee furnishes to the 4 [Assessing Officer], along with his return of`
  line `incomefor the assessment year concerned or within such further time as the 4 [Assessing Officer] may`
  line `allow, a certificate from the Tea Board as to the amount of such subsidy paid to the assessee during`
  line `the previous year.`
  line `Explanation. —In this clause, “Tea Board” means the Tea Board established under section 4 of`
  line `the Tea Act, 1953 (29 of 1953);]`
  line `5 [( 31 ) in the case of an assessee who carries on the business of growing and manufacturing`
  line `rubber, coffee, cardamom or such other commodity in India, as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf, the amount of any subsidy received from or`
  line `through the concerned Board under any such scheme for replantation or replacement of rubber plants,`
  line `coffee plants, cardamom plants or plants for the growing of such other commodity or for rejuvenation`
  line `or consolidation of areas used for cultivation of rubber, coffee, cardamom or such other commodity`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1969).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
