obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line 105
  line `Provided that the assessee furnishes to the Assessing Officer, along with his return of income for`
  line `the assessment year concerned or within such further time as the Assessing Officer may allow, a`
  line `certificate from the concerned Board, as to the amount of such subsidy paid to the assessee during the`
  line `previous year.`
  line `Explanation. —In this clause, “concerned Board” means,—`
  line `( i ) in relation to rubber, the Rubber Board constituted under section 4 of the Rubber Act,`
  line `1947 (24 of 1947),`
  line `( ii ) in relation to coffee, the Coffee Board constituted under section 4 of the Coffee Act, 1942`
  line `(7 of 1942),`
  line `( iii ) in relation to cardamom, the Spices Board constituted under section 3 of the Spices`
  line `Board Act, 1986 (10 of 1986),`
  line `( iv ) in relation to any other commodity specified under this clause, any Board or other`
  line `authority established under any law for the time being in force which the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf;]`
  line `1 [( 32 ) in the case of an assessee referred to in sub-section ( 1A ) of section 64, any income`
  line `includible in his total income under that sub-section, to the extent such income does not exceed one`
  line `thousand five hundred rupees in respect of each minor child whose income is so includible;]`
  line `2 [( 33 ) any income arising from the transfer of a capital asset, being a unit of the Unit`
  line `Scheme, 1964 referred to in Schedule I to the Unit Trust of India (Transfer of Undertaking and`
  line `Repeal) Act, 2002 (58 of 2002) and where the transfer of such asset takes place on or after the 1st day`
  line `of April, 2002;]`
  line `2 [( 34 ) any income by way of dividends referred to in section 115-O;`
  line `3 [Provided that nothing in this clause shall apply to any income by way of dividend chargeable to`
  line `tax in accordance with the provisions of section 115BBDA;]`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `5 [( 34A ) any income arising to an assessee, being a shareholder, on account of buy back of shares`
  line `(not being listed on a recognised stock exchange) by the company as referred to in section 115QA;]`
  line `( 35 ) any income by way of, —`
  line `( a ) income received in respect of the units of a Mutual Fund specified under clause ( 23D ); or`
  line `( b ) income received in respect of units from the Administrator of the specified`
  line `undertaking; or`
  line `( c ) income received in respect of units from the specified company:`
  line `Provided that this clause shall not apply to any income arising from transfer of units of the`
  line `Administrator of the specified undertaking or of the specified company or of a mutual fund, as the`
  line `case may be.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( a ) “Administrator” means the Administrator as referred to in clause ( a ) of section 2 of the`
  line `Unit Trust of India (Transfer of Undertaking and Repeal) Act, 2002 (58 of 2002);`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `4. The Explanation omitted by Act 8 of 2011, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-6-2011).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
