obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line 108
  line `( c ) “ recognised stock exchange” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( ii ) of`
  line `the Explanation 1 to sub-section ( 5 ) of section 43;]`
  line `1 [( 39 ) any specified income, arising from any international sporting event held in India, to the`
  line `person or persons notified by the Central Government in the Official Gazette, if such international`
  line `sporting event —`
  line `( a ) is approved by the international body regulating the international sport relating to such`
  line event;
  line `( b ) has participation by more than two countries;`
  line `( c ) is notified by the Central Government in the Official Gazette for the purposes of this`
  line clause.
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, “the specified income” means the income, of the`
  line `nature and to the extent, arising from the international sporting event, which the Central Government`
  line `may notify in this behalf;`
  line `( 40 ) any income of any subsidiary company by way of grant or otherwise received from an Indian`
  line `company, being its holding company engaged in the business of generation or transmission or`
  line `distribution of power if receipt of such income is for settlement of dues in connection with`
  line `reconstruction or revival of an existing business of power generation:`
  line `Provided that the provisions of this clause shall apply if reconstruction or revival of any existing`
  line `business of power generation is by way of transfer of such business to the Indian company notified`
  line `under sub-clause ( a ) of clause ( v ) of sub-section ( 4 ) of section 80-IA;`
  line `( 41 ) any income arising from transfer of a capital asset, being an asset of an undertaking engaged`
  line `in the business of generation or transmission or distribution of power where such transfer is effected`
  line `on or before the 31st day of March, 2006, to the Indian company notified under sub-clause ( a ) of`
  line `clause ( v ) of sub-section ( 4 ) of section 80-IA;]`
  line `2 [( 42 ) any specified income arising to a body or authority which —`
  line `( a ) has been established or constituted or appointed under a treaty or an agreement entered`
  line `into by the Central Government with two or more countries or a convention signed by the Central`
  line Government;
  line `( b ) is established or constituted or appointed not for the purposes of profit;`
  line `( c ) is notified by the Central Government in the Official Gazette for the purposes of this`
  line clause.
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, “specified income” means the income, of the`
  line `nature and to the extent, arising to the body or authority referred to in this clause, which the`
  line `Central Government may notify in this behalf;]`
  line `3 [( 43 ) any amount received by an individual as a loan, either in lump sum or in instalment, in a`
  line `transaction of reverse mortgage referred to in clause ( xvi ) of section 47;]`
  line `4 [( 44 ) any income received by any person for, or on behalf of, the New Pension System Trust`
  line `established on the 27th day of February, 2008 under the provisions of the Indian Trusts Act, 1882 (2`
  line `of 1882);]`
  line `5 [( 45 ) any allowance or perquisite, as may be notified by the Central Government in the Official`
  line `Gazette in this behalf, paid to the Chairman or a retired Chairman or any other member or retired`
  line `member of the Union Public Service Commission;]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 55 of 2005, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006. s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 43 of 2008, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
