obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line 110
  line `1 [( 50 ) any income arising from any specified service provided on or after the date on which the`
  line `provisions of Chapter VIII of the Finance Act, 2016 comes into force and chargeable to equalisation`
  line `levy under that Chapter.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, “specified service” shall have the meaning`
  line `assigned to it in clause (i) of section 164 of Chapter VIII of the Finance Act, 2016.]`
  line `2 [10A. Special provision in respect of newly established undertakings in free trade zone, etc. —`
  line `( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of this section, a deduction of such profits and gains as are derived by an`
  line `undertaking from the export of articles or things or computer software for a period of ten consecutive`
  line `assessment years beginning with the assessment year relevant to the previous year in which the`
  line `undertaking begins to manufacture or produce such articles or things or computer software, as the case`
  line `may be, shall be allowed from the total income of the assessee:`
  line `Provided that where in computing the total income of the undertaking for any assessment year, its`
  line `profits and gains had not been included by application of the provisions of this section as it stood`
  line `immediately before its substitution by the Finance Act, 2000, the undertaking shall be entitled to`
  line `deduction referred to in this sub-section only for the unexpired period of the aforesaid ten consecutive`
  line `assessment years:`
  line `Provided further that where an undertaking initially located in any free trade zone or export`
  line `processing zone is subsequently located in a special economic zone by reason of conversion of such free`
  line `trade zone or export processing zone into a special economic zone, the period of ten consecutive`
  line `assessment years referred to in this sub-section shall be reckoned from the assessment year relevant to the`
  line `previous year in which the 3 [undertaking began to manufacture or produce such articles or things or`
  line `computer software] in such free trade zone or export processing zone:`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `5 [Provided also that for the assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2003, the deduction`
  line `under this sub-section shall be ninety per cent. of the profits and gains derived by an undertaking from the`
  line `export of such articles or things or computer software:]`
  line `Provided also that no deduction under this section shall be allowed to any undertaking for the`
  line `assessment year beginning on the 6 [1st day of April, 2012] and subsequent years.`
  line `7 [( 1A ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), the deduction, in computing the total`
  line `income of an undertaking, which begins to manufacture or produce articles or things or computer`
  line `software during the previous year relevant to any assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2003, in any special economic zone, shall be, —`
  line `( i ) hundred per cent. of profits and gains derived from the export of such articles or things or`
  line `computer software for a period of five consecutive assessment years beginning with the assessment`
  line `year relevant to the previous year in which the undertaking begins to manufacture or produce such`
  line `articles or things or computer software, as the case may be, and thereafter, fifty per cent. of such`
  line `profits and gains for further two consecutive assessment years, and thereafter;`
  line `( ii ) for the next three consecutive assessment years, so much of the amount not exceeding fifty`
  line `per cent. of the profit as is debited to the profit and loss account of the previous year in respect of`
  line `which the deduction is to be allowed and credited to a reserve account (to be called the “ Special`
  line `Economic Zone Re- investment Allowance Reserve Account”) to be created and utilised for the`
  line `purposes of the business of the assessee in the manner laid down in sub-section ( 1B ):`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000. s. 6, for section 10A (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 6, for “undertaking was first set up” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2001).`
  line `4. The third proviso omitted by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 5, for “1st day of April, 2011” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2009).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
