obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line 112
  line `Explanation. — The provisions of Explanation 1 and Explanation 2 to sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 80-I shall apply for the purposes of clause ( iii ) of this sub-section as they apply for the purposes of`
  line `clause ( ii ) of that sub-section.`
  line `( 3 ) This section applies to the undertaking, if the sale proceeds of articles or things or computer`
  line `software exported out of India are received in, or brought into, India by the assessee in convertible foreign`
  line `exchange, within a period of six months from the end of the previous year or, within such further period`
  line `as the competent authority may allow in this behalf.`
  line `Explanation 1. — For the purposes of this sub- section, the expression “competent authority” means the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India or such other authority as is authorised under any law for the time being in force`
  line `for regulating payments and dealings in foreign exchange.`
  line `Explanation 2. — The sale proceeds referred to in this sub-section shall be deemed to have been`
  line `received in India where such sale proceeds are credited to a separate account maintained for the purpose`
  line `by the assessee with any bank outside India with the approval of the Reserve Bank of India.`
  line `1 [( 4 ) For the purposes of 2 [sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 1A )], the profits derived from export of articles or`
  line `things or computer software shall be the amount which bears to the profits of the business of the`
  line `undertaking, the same proportion as the export turnover in respect of such articles or things or computer`
  line `software bears to the total turnover of the business carried on by the undertaking.]`
  line `( 5 ) The deduction under 3 [this section] shall not be admissible for any assessment year beginning on`
  line `or after the 1st day of April, 2001, unless the assessee furnishes in the prescribed form, along with the`
  line `return of income, the report of an accountant, as defined in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 288, certifying that the deduction has been correctly claimed in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `this section.`
  line `( 6 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, in computing the total`
  line `income of the assessee of the previous year relevant to the assessment year immediately succeeding the`
  line `last of the relevant assessment years, or of any previous year, relevant to any subsequent assessment`
  line `year, —`
  line `( i ) section 32, section 32A, section 33, section 35 and clause ( ix ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section`
  line `36 shall apply as if every allowance or deduction referred to therein and relating to or allowable for`
  line `any of the relevant assessment years 4 [ending before the 1st day of April, 2001], in relation to any`
  line `building, machinery, plant or furniture used for the purposes of the business of the undertaking in the`
  line `previous year relevant to such assessment year or any expenditure incurred for the purposes of such`
  line `business in such previous year had been given full effect to for that assessment year itself and`
  line `accordingly sub-section ( 2 ) of section 32, clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 3 ) of section 32A, clause ( ii ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 33, sub-section ( 4 ) of section 35 or the second proviso to clause (ix) of sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ) of section 36, as the case may be, shall not apply in relation to any such allowance or`
  line deduction;
  line `( ii ) no loss referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 72 or sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 3 ) of`
  line `section 74, in so far as such loss relates to the business of the undertaking, shall be carried forward or`
  line `set off where such loss relates to any of the relevant assessment years 4 [ending before the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2001];`
  line `( iii ) no deduction shall be allowed under section 80HH or section 80HHA or section 80-I or`
  line `section 80-IA or section 80-IB in relation to the profits and gains of the undertaking; and`
  line `( iv ) in computing the depreciation allowance under section 32, the written down value of any`
  line `asset used for the purposes of the business of the undertaking shall be computed as if the assessee had`
  line `claimed and been actually allowed the deduction in respect of depreciation for each of the relevant`
  line `assessment year.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 7, for “sub -section ( 1 )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2003).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for “sub -section ( 1 )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2003).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
