obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line 114
  line `( v ) “ free trade zone ” means the Kandla Free Trade Zone and the Santacruz Electronics Export`
  line `Processing Zone and includes any other free trade zone which the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify for the purposes of this section;`
  line `( vi ) “relevant assessment year” means any assessment year falling within a period of ten`
  line `consecutive assessment years referred to in this section;`
  line `( vii ) “software technology park” means any park set up in accordance with the Software`
  line `Technology Park Scheme notified by the Government of India in the Ministry of Commerce and`
  line Industry;
  line `( viii ) “special economic zone” means a zone which the Central Government may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, specify as a special economic zone for the purposes of this section.]`
  line `1 [ Explanation 3. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the profits and gains derived`
  line `from on site development of computer software (including services for development of software) outside`
  line `India shall be deemed to be the profits and gains derived from the export of computer software outside`
  line India.]
  line `2 [ Explanation 4. —For the purposes of this section, “manufacture or produce” shall include the cutting`
  line `and polishing of precious and semi-precious stones.]`
  line `10AA. 3 [ Special provisions in respect of newly established Units in Special Economic Zones. — ( 1 )`
  line `Subject to the provisions of this section, in computing the total income of an assessee, being an`
  line `entrepreneur as referred to in clause ( j ) of section 2 of the Special Economic Zones Act, 2005, from his`
  line `Unit, who begins to manufacture or produce articles or things or provide any services during the previous`
  line `year relevant to any assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of 4 [April, 2006, a deduction`
  line `of] —`
  line `( i ) hundred per cent. of profits and gains derived from the export, of such articles or things or`
  line `from services for a period of five consecutive assessment years beginning with the assessment year`
  line `relevant to the previous year in which the Unit begins to manufacture or produce such articles or`
  line `things or provide services, as the case may be, and fifty per cent. of such profits and gains for further`
  line `five assessment years and thereafter;`
  line `( ii ) for the next five consecutive assessment years, so much of the amount not exceeding fifty per`
  line `cent. of the profit as is debited to the profit and loss account of the previous year in respect of which`
  line `the deduction is to be allowed and credited to a reserve account (to be called the “Special Economic`
  line `Zone Re- investment Reserve Account”) to be c reated and utilized for the purposes of the business of`
  line `the assessee in the manner laid down in sub-section ( 2 ).`
  line `5 [ Explanation. –– For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the amount of deduction`
  line `under this section shall be allowed from the total income of the assessee computed in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of this Act, before giving effect to the provisions of this section and the deduction`
  line `under this section shall not exceed such total income of the assessee.]`
  line `( 2 ) The deduction under clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) shall be allowed only if the following conditions`
  line `are fulfilled, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the amount credited to the Special Economic Zone Re-investment Reserve Account is to be`
  line `utilised —`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 28 of 2005, s. 27 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 10-2-2006).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 8, for the words, figures and letters “April, 2006, a deduction of” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `5. Ins. Act 7 of 2017, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
