  title `Page 116`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  sourcePage 116
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line 116
  line `1 [( 4 ) This section applies to any undertaking, being the Unit, which fulfils all the following`
  line `conditions, namely: —`
  line `( i ) it has begun or begins to manufacture or produce articles or things or provide services during`
  line `the previous year relevant to the assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 2006`
  line `in any Special Economic Zone;`
  line `( ii ) it is not formed by the splitting up, or the reconstruction, of a business already in existence:`
  line `Provided that this condition shall not apply in respect of any undertaking, being the Unit, which is`
  line `formed as a result of the re-establishment, reconstruction or revival by the assessee of the business of`
  line `any such undertaking as is referred to in section 33B, in the circumstances and within the period`
  line `specified in that section;`
  line `( iii ) it is not formed by the transfer to a new business, of machinery or plant previously used for`
  line `any purpose.`
  line `Explanation. — The provisions of Explanations 1 and 2 to sub-section ( 3 ) of section 80-IA shall apply`
  line `for the purposes of clause ( iii ) of this sub-section as they apply for the purposes of clause ( ii ) of that sub-`
  line section.]
  line `( 5 ) Where any undertaking being the Unit which is entitled to the deduction under this section is`
  line `transferred, before the expiry of the period specified in this section, to another undertaking, being the Unit`
  line `in a scheme of amalgamation or demerger, —`
  line `( a ) no deduction shall be admissible under this section to the amalgamating or the demerged Unit,`
  line `being the company for the previous year in which the amalgamation or the demerger takes place; and`
  line `( b ) the provisions of this section shall, as they would have applied to the amalgamating or the`
  line `demerged Unit being the company as if the amalgamation or demerger had not taken place.`
  line `( 6 ) Loss referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 72 or sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 3 ) of section 74,`
  line `in so far as such loss relates to the business of the undertaking, being the Unit shall be allowed to be`
  line `carried forward or set off.`
  line `( 7 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), the profits derived from the export of articles or things or`
  line `services (including computer software) shall be the amount which bears to the profits of the business of`
  line `the undertaking, being the Unit, the same proportion as the export turnover in respect of such articles or`
  line `things or services bears to the total turnover of the business carried on 2 [by the undertaking]:`
  line `3 [Provided that the provisions of this sub-section [as amended by section 6 of the Finance (No. 2)`
  line `Act, 2009 (33 of 2009)] shall have effect for the assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2006`
  line `and subsequent assessment years.]`
  line `( 8 ) The provisions of sub-sections ( 5 ) and ( 6 ) of section 10A shall apply to the articles or things or`
  line `services referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) as if —`
  line `( a ) for the fig ures, letters and word “1st April, 2001”, the figures, letters and word “1st April,`
  line `2006” had been substituted;`
  line `( b ) for the word “undertaking”, the words “undertaking, being the Unit” had been substituted.`
  line `( 9 ) The provisions of sub-section ( 8 ) and sub-section ( 10 ) of section 80-IA shall, so far as may be,`
  line `apply in relation to the undertaking referred to in this section as they apply for the purposes of the`
  line `undertaking referred to in section 80-IA.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 7, for certain words (w.e.f. 10-2-2006).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 6, for “by the assessee” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2010).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-117
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 117
  title `Page 117`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  sourcePage 117
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line 117
  line `1 [( 10 ) Where a deduction under this section is claimed and allowed in respect of profits of any of the`
  line `specified business, referred to in clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 8 ) of section 35AD, for any assessment year,`
  line `no deduction shall be allowed under the provisions of section 35AD in relation to such specified business`
  line `for the same or any other assessment year.]`
  line `Explanation 1. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “export turnover” means the consideration in respect of export by the undertaking, being the`
  line `Unit of articles or things or services received in, or brought into, India by the assessee but does not`
  line `include freight, telecommunication charges or insurance attributable to the delivery of the articles or`
  line `things outside India or expenses, if any, incurred in foreign exchange in rendering of services`
  line `(including computer software) outside India;`
  line `( ii ) “export in relation to the Special Economic Zones” means taking goods or providing services`
  line `out of India from a Special Economic Zone by land, sea, air, or by any other mode, whether physical`
  line `or otherwise;`
  line `( iii ) “manufacture” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause ( r ) of section 2 of the`
  line `Special Economic Zones Act, 2005;`
  line `( iv ) “relevant assessment year” means any assessment year falling within a period of fifteen`
  line `consecutive assessment years referred to in this section;`
  line `( v ) “Special Economic Zone” and “Unit” shall have the same meanings as assigned to them`
  line `under clauses ( za ) and ( zc ) of section 2 of the Special Economic Zones Act, 2005.`
  line `Explanation 2. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the profits and gains derived`
  line `from on site development of computer software (including services for development of software) outside`
  line `India shall be deemed to be the profits and gains derived from the export of computer software outside`
  line India.]
  line `2 [10B. Special provisions in respect of newly established hundred per cent. export-oriented`
  line `undertakings. — ( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of this section, a deduction of such profits and gains as are`
  line `derived by a hundred per cent. export-oriented undertaking from the export of articles or things or`
  line `computer software for a period of ten consecutive assessment years beginning with the assessment year`
  line `relevant to the previous year in which the undertaking begins to manufacture or produce articles or things`
  line `or computer software, as the case may be, shall be allowed from the total income of the assessee:`
  line `Provided that where in computing the total income of the undertaking for any assessment year, its`
  line `profits and gains had not been included by application of the provisions of this section as it stood`
  line `immediately before its substitution by the Finance Act, 2000, the undertaking shall be entitled to the`
  line `deduction referred to in this sub-section only for the unexpired period of aforesaid ten consecutive`
  line `assessment years:`
  line `3 [Provided 4 [further] that for the assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2003, the`
  line `deduction under this sub-section shall be ninety per cent. of the profits and gains derived by an`
  line `undertaking from the export of such articles or things or computer software:]`
  line `Provided also that no deduction under this section shall be allowed to any undertaking for the`
  line `assessment year beginning on the 5 [1st day of April, 2012] and subsequent years:`
  line `6 [Provided also that no deduction under this section shall be allowed to an assessee who does not`
  line `furnish a return of his income on or before the due date specified under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 6, (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 7, for section 10B (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 5, for “also” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009 s. 7, for “1st day of April 2011” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2009).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-118
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 118
  title `Page 118`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  sourcePage 118
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line 118
  line `( 2 ) This section applies to any undertaking which fulfils all the following conditions, namely: —`
  line `( i ) it manufactures or produces any articles or things or computer software;`
  line `( ii ) it is not formed by the splitting up, or the reconstruction, of a business already in existence:`
  line `Provided that this condition shall not apply in respect of any undertaking which is formed as a`
  line `result of the re-establishment, reconstruction or revival by the assessee of the business of any such`
  line `undertaking as is referred to in section 33B, in the circumstances and within the period specified in`
  line `that section;`
  line `( iii ) it is not formed by the transfer to a new business of machinery or plant previously used for`
  line `any purpose.`
  line `Explanation. — The provisions of Explanation 1 and Explanation 2 to sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 80-I shall apply for the purposes of clause ( iii ) of this sub-section as they apply for the purposes of`
  line `clause ( ii ) of that sub-section.`
  line `( 3 ) This section applies to the undertaking, if the sale proceeds of articles or things or computer`
  line `software exported out of India are received in, or brought into, India by the assessee in convertible foreign`
  line `exchange, within a period of six months from the end of the previous year or, within such further period`
  line `as the competent authority may allow in this behalf.`
  line `Explanation 1. — For the purposes of this sub- section, the expression “competent authority” means the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India or such other authority as is authorised under any law for the time being in force`
  line `for regulating payments and dealings in foreign exchange.`
  line `Explanation 2. — The sale proceeds referred to in this sub-section shall be deemed to have been`
  line `received in India where such sale proceeds are credited to a separate account maintained for the purpose`
  line `by the assessee with any bank outside India with the approval of the Reserve Bank of India.`
  line `1 [( 4 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), the profits derived from export of articles or things or`
  line `computer software shall be the amount which bears to the profits of the business of the undertaking, the`
  line `same proportion as the export turnover in respect of such articles or things or computer software bears to`
  line `the total turnover of the business carried on by the undertaking.]`
  line `( 5 ) The deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall not be admissible for any assessment year beginning on`
  line `or after the 1st day of April, 2001, unless the assessee furnishes in the prescribed form, along with the`
  line `return of income, the report of an accountant, as defined in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 288, certifying that the deduction has been correctly claimed in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of this section.`
  line `( 6 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, in computing the total`
  line `income of the assessee of the previous year relevant to the assessment year immediately succeeding the`
  line `last of the relevant assessment years, or of any previous year, relevant to any subsequent assessment`
  line `year, —`
  line `( i ) section 32, section 32A, section 33, section 35 and clause ( ix ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 35 shall apply as if every allowance or deduction referred to therein and relating to or`
  line `allowable for any of the relevant assessment years 2 [ending before the 1st day of April, 2001], in`
  line `relation to any building, machinery, plant or furniture used for the purposes of the business of the`
  line `undertaking in the previous year relevant to such assessment year or any expenditure incurred for the`
  line `purposes of such business in such previous year had been given full effect to for that assessment year`
  line `itself and accordingly sub-section ( 2 ) of section 32, clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 3 ) of section 32A,`
  line `clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 33,, sub-section ( 4 ) of section 35 or the second proviso to`
  line `clause ( ix ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 36, as the case may be, shall not apply in relation to any such`
  line `allowance or deduction;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 7, for sub-section ( 4 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 8, (w.r.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
