obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line 119
  line `( ii ) no loss referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 72 or sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 3 )`
  line `of section 74, in so far as such loss relates to the business of the undertaking, shall be carried forward`
  line `or set-off where such loss relates to any of the relevant assessment years 1 [ending before the 1st day`
  line `of April, 2001;]`
  line `( iii ) no deduction shall be allowed under section 80HH or section 80HHA or`
  line `section 80-I or section 80IA or section 80-IB in relation to the profits and gains of the undertaking;`
  line and
  line `( iv ) in computing the depreciation allowance under section 32, the written down value of any`
  line `asset used for the purposes of the business of the undertaking shall be computed as if the assessee had`
  line `claimed and been actually allowed the deduction in respect of depreciation for each of the relevant`
  line `assessment year.`
  line `( 7 ) The provisions of sub-section ( 8 ) and sub-section ( 10 ) of section 80-IA shall, so far as may be,`
  line `apply in relation to the undertaking referred to in this section as they apply for the purposes of the`
  line `undertaking referred to in section 80-IA.`
  line `2 [( 7A ) Where any undertaking of an Indian company which is entitled to the deduction under this`
  line `section is transferred, before the expiry of the period specified in this section, to another Indian company`
  line `in a scheme of amalgamation or demerger —`
  line `( a ) no deduction shall be admissible under this section to the amalgamating or the demerged`
  line `company for the previous year in which the amalgamation or the demerger takes place; and`
  line `( b ) the provisions of this section shall, as far as may be, apply to the amalgamated or resulting`
  line `company as they would have applied to the amalgamating or the demerged company if the`
  line `amalgamation or the demerger had not taken place.]`
  line `( 8 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, where the`
  line `assessee, before the due date for furnishing the return of income under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139,`
  line `furnishes to the Assessing Officer a declaration in writing that the provisions of this section may not be`
  line `made applicable to him, the provisions of this section shall not apply to him for any of the relevant`
  line `assessment year.`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `Explanation 2. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “computer software” means —`
  line `( a ) any computer programme recorded on any disc, tape, perforated media or other`
  line `information storage device; or`
  line `( b ) any customized electronic data or any product or service of similar nature as may be`
  line `notified by the Board,`
  line `which is transmitted or exported from India to any place outside India by any means;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 8 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `3. Clause ( 9 ) omitted by, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `4. Clause ( 9A ) omitted by s. 8 ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `5. Explanation 1 omittedby s. 8 ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
