obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line 120
  line `( ii ) “ convertible foreign exchange” means foreign exchange which is for the time being treated by`
  line `the Reserve Bank of India as convertible foreign exchange for the purposes of 1 [the Foreign Exchange`
  line `Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999)], and any rules made thereunder or any other corresponding law`
  line `for the time being in force;`
  line `( iii ) “export turnover” means the consideration 2 [in respect of export by the undertaking] of`
  line `articles or things or computer software received in, or brought into, India by the assessee in`
  line `convertible foreign exchange in accordance with sub-section ( 3 ), but does not include freight,`
  line `telecommunication charges or insurance attributable to the delivery of the articles or things or`
  line `computer software outside India or expenses, if any, incurred in foreign exchange in providing the`
  line `technical services outside India;`
  line `( iv ) “hundred per cent. export- oriented undertaking” means an undertaking which has been`
  line `approved as a hundred per cent. export-oriented undertaking by the Board appointed in this behalf by`
  line `the Central Government in exercise of the powers conferred by section 14 of the Industries`
  line `(Development and Regulation) Act, 1951 (65 of 1951), and the rules made under that Act;`
  line `( v ) “relevant assessment years” means any assessment years falling within a period of ten`
  line `consecutive assessment years, referred to in this section.]`
  line `3 [ Explanation 3. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the profits and gains derived`
  line `from on site development of computer software (including services for development of software) outside`
  line `India shall be deemed to be the profits and gains derived from the export of computer software outside`
  line India.]
  line `4 [ Explanation 4. — For the purposes of this section, “manufacture or produce” shall include the cutting`
  line `and polishing of precious and semi-precious stones.]`
  line `5 [ 10BA. Special provisions in respect of export of certain articles or things. — ( 1 ) Subject to the`
  line `provisions of this section, a deduction of such profits and gains as are derived by an undertaking from the`
  line `export out of India of eligible articles or things, shall be allowed from the total income of the assessee:`
  line `Provided that where in computing the total income of the undertaking for any assessment year,`
  line `deduction under section 10A or section 10B has been claimed, the undertaking shall not be entitled to the`
  line `deduction under this section:`
  line `Provided further that no deduction under this section shall be allowed to any undertaking for the`
  line `assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2010 and subsequent years.`
  line `( 2 ) This section applies to any undertaking which fulfils the following conditions, namely: —`
  line `( a ) it manufactures or produces the eligible articles or things without the use of imported raw`
  line materials;
  line `( b ) it is not formed by the splitting up, or the reconstruction, of a business already in existence:`
  line `Provided that this condition shall not apply in respect of any undertaking which is formed as a`
  line `result of the re-establishment, reconstruction or revival by the assessee of the business of any such`
  line `undertaking as is referred to in section 33B, in the circumstances and within the period specified in`
  line `that section;`
  line `( c ) it is not formed by the transfer to a new business of machinery or plant previously used for`
  line `any purpose.`
  line `Explanation. — The provisions of Explanation 1 and Explanation 2 to sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 80-I shall apply for the purposes of this clause as they apply for the purposes of clause ( ii ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of that section;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 4, for “the Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 7, for the words “in the respect of export” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2001).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
