obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line 121
  line `( d ) ninety per cent. or more of its sales during the previous year relevant to the assessment year`
  line `are by way of exports of the eligible articles or things;`
  line `( e ) it employs twenty or more workers during the previous year in the process of manufacture or`
  line production.
  line `( 3 ) This section applies to the undertaking, if the sale proceeds of the eligible articles or things`
  line `exported out of India are received in or brought into, India by the assessee in convertible foreign`
  line `exchange, within a period of six months from the end of the previous year or, within such further period`
  line `as the competent authority may allow in this behalf.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- section, the expression “competent authority” means the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India or such other authority as is authorised under any law for the time being in force`
  line `for regulating payments and dealings in foreign exchange.`
  line `( 4 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), the profits derived from export out of India of the eligible`
  line `articles or things shall be the amount which bears to the profits of the business of the undertaking, the`
  line `same proportion as the export turnover in respect of such articles or things bears to the total turnover of`
  line `the business carried on by the undertaking.`
  line `( 5 ) The deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall not be admissible, unless the assessee furnishes in the`
  line `prescribed form, along with the return of income, the report of an accountant, as defined in`
  line `the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288, certifying that the deduction has been correctly`
  line `claimed in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line `( 6 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, where a deduction is`
  line `allowed under this section in computing the total income of the assessee, no deduction shall be allowed`
  line `under any other section in respect of its export profits.`
  line `( 7 ) The provisions of sub-section ( 8 ) and sub-section ( 10 ) of section 80-IA shall, so far as may be,`
  line `apply in relation to the undertaking referred to in this section as they apply for the purposes of the`
  line `undertaking referred to in section 80-IA.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “convertible foreign exchange” means foreign exchange which is for the time being treated by`
  line `the Reserve Bank of India as convertible foreign exchange for the purposes of the Foreign Exchange`
  line `Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999), and any rules made thereunder or any other corresponding law`
  line `for the time being in force;`
  line `( b ) “eligible articles or things” means all hand -made articles or things, which are of artistic value`
  line `and which requires the use of wood as the main raw material;`
  line `( c ) “export turnover” means the consideration in respect of export by the undertaking of eligible`
  line `articles or things received in, or brought into, India by the assessee in convertible foreign exchange in`
  line `accordance with sub-section ( 3 ), but does not include freight, telecommunication charges or insurance`
  line `attributable to the delivery of the articles or things outside India;`
  line `( d ) “export out of India” shall not include any transac tion by way of sale or otherwise, in a shop,`
  line `emporium or any other establishment situate in India, not involving clearance of any customs station`
  line `as defined in the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962).]`
  line `1 [10BB. Meaning of computer programmes in certain cases. — The profits and gains derived by an`
  line `undertaking from the production of computer programmes under section 10B, as it stood prior to its`
  line `substitution by section 7 of the Finance Act, 2000 (10 of 2000), shall be construed as if for the words`
  line `“computer programmes”, the words “computer programmes or processing or management of electronic`
  line `data” had been substituted in that section.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-1994).`
