  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  sourcePage 122
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line 122
  line `1 [10C. Special provision in respect of certain industrial undertakings in North-Eastern`
  line `Region. — ( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of this section, any profits and gains derived by an assessee from`
  line `an industrial undertaking, which has begun or begins to manufacture or produce any article or thing on or`
  line `after the 1st day of April, 1998 in any Integrated Infrastructure Development Centre or Industrial Growth`
  line `Centre located in the North-Eastern Region (hereafter in this section referred to as the industrial`
  line `undertaking) shall not be included in the total income of the assessee.`
  line `( 2 ) This section applies to any industrial undertaking which fulfils all the following conditions,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( i ) it is not formed by the splitting up, or the reconstruction of, a business already in existence:`
  line `Provided that this condition shall not apply in respect of any industrial undertaking which is`
  line `formed as a result of the re-establishment, reconstruction or revival by the assessee of the business of`
  line `any such industrial undertaking as is referred to in section 33B, in the circumstances and within the`
  line `period specified in that section;`
  line `( ii ) it is not formed by the transfer to a new business of machinery or plant previously used for`
  line `any purpose.`
  line `Explanation. — The provisions of Explanation 1 and Explanation 2 to sub-section ( 3 ) of`
  line `section 80-IA shall apply for the purposes of clause ( ii ) of this sub-section as they apply for the purposes`
  line `of clause ( ii ) of that sub-section.`
  line `( 3 ) The profits and gains referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall not be included in the total income of the`
  line `assessee in respect of ten consecutive assessment years beginning with the assessment year relevant to the`
  line `previous year in which the industrial undertaking begins to manufacture or produce articles or things.`
  line `( 4 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, in computing the total`
  line `income of the assessee of any previous year relevant to any subsequent assessment year, —`
  line `( i ) section 32, section 35 and clause ( ix ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 36 shall apply as if`
  line `deduction referred to therein and relating to or allowable for any of the relevant assessment years, in`
  line `relation to any building, machinery, plant or furniture used for the purposes of the business of the`
  line `industrial undertaking in the previous year relevant to such assessment year or any expenditure`
  line `incurred for the purposes of such business in such previous year had been given full effect to for that`
  line `assessment year itself and, accordingly, sub-section ( 2 ) of section 32, sub-section ( 4 ) of section 35 or`
  line `the second proviso to clause ( ix ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 36, as the case may be, shall not apply`
  line `in relation to any such deduction;`
  line `( ii ) no loss referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 72 or sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 3 )`
  line `of section 74, in so far as such loss relates to the business of the industrial undertaking, shall be`
  line `carried forward or set off where such loss relates to any of the relevant assessment years;`
  line `( iii ) no deduction shall be allowed under section 80HH or section 80HHA or`
  line `section 80-I or section 80-IA or section 80-IB or section 80JJA in relation to the profits and gains of`
  line `the industrial undertakings; and`
  line `( iv ) in computing the depreciation allowance under section 32, the written down value of any`
  line `asset used for the purposes of the business of the industrial undertaking shall be computed as if the`
  line `assessee had claimed and been actually allowed the deduction in respect of depreciation for each of`
  line `the relevant assessment years.`
  line `( 5 ) The provisions of sub-section ( 8 ) and sub-section ( 10 ) of section 80-IA shall, so far as may be,`
  line `apply in relation to the industrial undertaking referred to in this section as they apply for the purposes of`
  line `the industrial undertaking referred to in section 80-IA or section 80IB, as the case may be.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
