obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line 123
  line `( 6 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, where the assessee`
  line `before the due date for furnishing the return of his income under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139, furnishes`
  line `to the Assessing Officer a declaration in writing that the provisions of this section may not be made`
  line `applicable to him, the provisions of this section shall not apply to him in any of the relevant assessment`
  line `years:`
  line `1 [Provided that no deduction under this section shall be allowed to any undertaking for the assessment`
  line `year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2004 and subsequent years.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “Integrated Infrastructure Development Centre” means such centres located in the States of the`
  line `North-Eastern Region, which the Central Government, may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `specify for the purposes of this section;`
  line `( ii ) “Industrial Growth Centre” means such centres located in the States of the North -Eastern`
  line `Region, which the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify for the`
  line `purposes of this section;`
  line `( iii ) “North - Eastern Region” means the region comprising the States of Arunachal Pradesh,`
  line `Assam, Manipur, Meghalaya, Mizoram, Nagaland, Sikkim and Tripura;`
  line `( iv ) “relevant assessment years” means the ten consecutive years beginning with the year in`
  line `which the industrial undertaking begins to manufacture or produce articles or things.]`
  line `2 [11. Income from property held for charitable or religious purposes. — ( 1 ) Subject to the`
  line `provisions of sections 60 to 63, the following income shall not be included in the total income of the`
  line `previous year of the person in receipt of the income —`
  line `3 [( a ) income derived from property held under trust wholly for charitable or religious purposes, to`
  line `the extent to which such income is applied to such purposes in India; and, where any such income is`
  line `accumulated or set apart for application to such purposes in India, to the extent to which the income`
  line `so accumulated or set apart is not in excess of 4 [fifteen per cent.] of the income from such property;`
  line `( b ) income derived from property held under trust in part only for such purposes, the trust having`
  line `been created before the commencement of this Act, to the extent to which such income is applied to`
  line `such purposes in India; and, where any such income is finally set apart for application to such`
  line `purposes in India, to the extent to which the income so set apart is not in excess of 4 [fifteen per cent.]`
  line `of the income from such property;`
  line `( c ) income 5 [derived from property held under trust] —`
  line `( i ) created on or after the 1st day of April, 1952, for a charitable purpose which tends to`
  line `promote international welfare in which India is interested, to the extent to which such income is`
  line `applied to such purposes outside India, and`
  line `( ii ) for charitable or religious purposes, created before the 1st day of April, 1952, to the extent`
  line `to which such income is applied to such purposes outside India:`
  line `Provided that the Board, by general or special order, has directed in either case that it shall not be`
  line `included in the total income of the person in receipt of such income;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `2. Section 11 restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 with amendments (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 7`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 4, for clauses ( a ) and ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 7, for “twenty - five per cent.” (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-124
  sectionNo (124)
