  title `Page 124`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  sourcePage 124
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line 124
  line `1 [( d ) income in the form of voluntary contributions made with a specific direction that they shall`
  line `form part of the corpus of the trust or institution.`
  line `2 [ Explanation 3 [1]. — For the purposes of clauses ( a ) and ( b ), —`
  line `( 1 ) in computing the 4 [fifteen per cent.] of the income which may be accumulated or set apart,`
  line `any such voluntary contributions as are referred to in section 12 shall be deemed to be part of the`
  line income;
  line `( 2 ) if, in the previous year, the income applied to charitable or religious purposes in India falls`
  line `short of 5 [eighty-five per cent.] of the income derived during that year from property held under trust,`
  line `or, as the case may be, held under trust in part, by any amount —`
  line `( i ) for the reason that the whole or any part of the income has not been received during that`
  line `year, or`
  line `( ii ) for any other reason,`
  line `then —`
  line `( a ) in the case referred to in sub-clause ( i ), so much of the income applied to such purposes in`
  line `India during the previous year in which the income is received or during the previous year`
  line `immediately following as does not exceed the said amount, and`
  line `( b ) in the case referred to in sub-clause ( ii ), so much of the income applied to such purposes`
  line `in India during the previous year immediately following the previous year in which the income`
  line `was derived as does not exceed the said amount,`
  line `may, at the option of the person in receipt of the income 6 [(such option to be exercised before the expiry`
  line `of the time allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139 for furnishing the return of income, in such form`
  line `and manner as may be prescribed)] be deemed to be income applied to such purposes during the previous`
  line `year in which the income was derived; and the income so deemed to have been applied shall not be taken`
  line `into account in calculating the amount of income applied to such purposes, in the case referred to in sub-`
  line `clause ( i ), during the previous year in which the income is received or during the previous year`
  line `immediately following, as the case may be, and, in the case referred to in sub-clause ( ii ), during the`
  line `previous year immediately following the previous year in which the income was derived.]`
  line `7 [ Explanation 2. — Any amount credited or paid, out of income referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b )`
  line `read with Explanation 1, to any other trust or institution registered under section 12AA, being`
  line `contribution with a specific direction that they shall form part of the corpus of the trust or institution, shall`
  line `not be treated as application of income for charitable or religious purposes.]`
  line `8 [ Explanation 3. — For the purposes of determining the amount of application under clause (a) or`
  line `clause (b), the provisions of sub-clause (ia) of clause (a) of section 40 and sub-sections (3) and (3A) of`
  line `section 40A, shall, mutatis mutandis, apply as they apply in computing the income chargeable under the`
  line `head “Profits and gains of business or profession. ]`
  line `9 [( 1A ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), —`
  line `( a ) where a capital asset, being property held under trust wholly for charitable or religious`
  line `purposes, is transferred and the whole or any part of the net consideration is utilised for acquiring`
  line `another capital asset to be so held, then, the capital gain arising from the transfer shall be deemed to`
  line `have been applied to charitable or religious purposes to the extent specified hereunder, namely: —`
  line `( i ) where the whole of the net consideration is utilised in acquiring the new capital asset, the`
  line `whole of such capital gain;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 4, for Explanation (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `3. The Explanation renumbered as Explanation 1 thereof by Act 7 of 2017, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 7 for “twenty - five per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2003).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for “seventy - five per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2003).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 8, for “(such option to be exercised in writing before the expiry of the time allowed under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139 for furnishing the return of income)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2016).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 32 of 1971, s. 5 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-125
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 125
  title `Page 125`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  sourcePage 125
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line 125
  line `( ii ) where only a part of the net consideration is utilised for acquiring the new capital asset, so`
  line `much of such capital gain as is equal to the amount, if any, by which the amount so utilised`
  line `exceeds the cost of the transferred asset;`
  line `( b ) where a capital asset, being property held under trust in part only for such purposes, is`
  line `transferred and the whole or any part of the net consideration is utilised for acquiring another capital`
  line `asset to be so held, then, the appropriate fraction of the capital gain arising from the transfer shall be`
  line `deemed to have been applied to charitable or religious purposes to the extent specified hereunder,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( i ) where the whole of the net consideration is utilised in acquiring the new capital asset, the`
  line `whole of the appropriate fraction of such capital gain;`
  line `( ii ) in any other case, so much of the appropriate fraction of the capital gain as is equal to the`
  line `amount, if any, by which the appropriate fraction of the amount utilised for acquiring the new`
  line `asset exceeds the appropriate fraction of the cost of the transferred asset.`
  line `Explanation. — In this sub-section, —`
  line `( i ) “appropriate fraction” means the fraction which represents the extent to which the income`
  line `derived from the capital asset transferred was immediately before such transfer applicable to`
  line `charitable or religious purposes;`
  line `( ii ) “cost of the transferred asset” means the aggregate of the cost of acquisition (as`
  line `ascertained for the purposes of section 48 and 49) of the capital asset which is the subject of the`
  line `transfer and the cost of any improvement thereto within the meaning assigned to that expression`
  line `in sub-clause ( b ) of clause ( 1 ) of section 55;`
  line `( iii ) “net consideration” means the full value of the consideration received or accruing as a`
  line `result of the transfer of the capital asset as reduced by any expenditure incurred wholly and`
  line `exclusively in connection with such transfer.]`
  line `1 [( 1B ) Where any income in respect of which an option is exercised under clause ( 2 ) of`
  line `the Explanation to sub-section ( 1 ) is not applied to charitable or religious purposes in India during the`
  line `period referred to in sub-clause ( a ) or, as the case may be, sub-clause ( b ), of the said clause, then, such`
  line `income shall be deemed to be the income of the person in receipt thereof —`
  line `( a ) in the case referred to in sub-clause ( i ) of the said clause, of the previous year immediately`
  line `following the previous year in which the income was received; or`
  line `( b ) in the case referred to in sub-clause ( ii ) of the said clause, of the previous year immediately`
  line `following the previous year in which the income was derived.`
  line `2 [( 2 ) 3 [Where 4 [eighty-five per cent.] of the income referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) read with the Explanation to that sub-section is not applied, or is not deemed to have been`
  line `applied, to charitable or religious purposes in India during the previous year but is accumulated or set`
  line `apart, either in whole or in part, for application to such purposes in India, such income so accumulated or`
  line `set apart shall not be included in the total income of the previous year of the person in receipt of the`
  line `income, provided the following conditions are complied with, namely: — ]`
  line `5 [( a ) such person furnishes a statement in the prescribed form and in the prescribed 3 manner to`
  line `the Assessing Officer, stating the purpose for which the income is being accumulated or set apart and`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 19 of 1970, s. 5, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 4, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 7, for “seventy - five per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2003).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 8, for clauses ( a ), ( b ) and the first and second provisos (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
