obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line 127
  line `1 [Provided that the 2 [Assessing Officer] shall not allow application of such income by way of`
  line `payment or credit made for the purposes referred to in clause ( d ) of sub-section ( 3 ) of section 11:]`
  line `3 [Provided further that in case the trust or institution, which has invested or deposited its income in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 2 ), is dissolved, the 2 [Assessing Officer] may`
  line `allow application of such income for the purposes referred to in clause ( d ) of sub-section ( 3 ) in the year in`
  line `which such trust or institution was dissolved.]`
  line `( 4 ) For the pur poses of this section “property held under trust” includes a business undertaking so`
  line `held, and where a claim is made that the income of any such undertaking shall not be included in the total`
  line `income of the persons in receipt thereof, the 2 [Assessing Officer] shall have power to determine the`
  line `income of such undertaking in accordance with the provisions of this Act relating to assessment; and`
  line `where any income so determined is in excess of the income as shown in the accounts of the undertaking,`
  line `such excess shall be deemed to be applied to purposes other than charitable or religious purposes 4 ***.`
  line `5 [( 4A ) Sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 3A ) shall not apply in`
  line `relation to any income of a trust or an institution, being profits and gains of business, unless the business`
  line `is incidental to the attainment of the objectives of the trust or, as the case may be, institution, and separate`
  line `books of account are maintained by such trust or institution in respect of such business.]`
  line `6 [( 5 ) The forms and modes of investing or depositing the money referred to in clause ( b ) of sub-`
  line `section ( 2 ) shall be the following, namely: —`
  line `( i ) investment in savings certificates as defined in clause (c) of section 2 of the Government`
  line `Savings Certificates Act, 1959 (46 of 1959), and any other securities or certificates issued by the`
  line `Central Government under the Small Savings Schemes of that Government;`
  line `( ii ) deposit in any account with the Post Office Savings Bank;`
  line `( iii ) deposit in any account with a scheduled bank or a co-operative society engaged in carrying`
  line `on the business of banking (including a co-operative land mortgage bank or a co-operative land`
  line `development bank).`
  line `Explanation. —In this clause, “scheduled bank” means the State Bank of India constituted und er`
  line `the State Bank of India Act, 1955 (23 of 1955), a subsidiary bank as defined in the State Bank of`
  line `India (Subsidiary Banks) Act, 1959 (38 of 1959), a corresponding new bank constituted under section`
  line `3 of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970), or`
  line `under section 3 of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1980 (40`
  line `of 1980), or any other bank being a bank included in the Second Schedule to the Reserve Bank of`
  line `India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line `( iv ) investment in units of the Unit Trust of India established under the Unit Trust of India Act,`
  line `1963 (52 of 1963);`
  line `( v ) investment in any security for money created and issued by the Central Government or a`
  line `State Government;`
  line `1. Ins. byAct 20 of 2002, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `4. The words brackets and figures “and accordingly chargeable to tax within the meaning of sub -section ( 3 )” omitted by`
  line `Act 19 of 1970, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 6, for sub-section ( 4A ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `6.Ins. by Act 11 of 1983, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-1984).`
