obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line 128
  line `( vi ) investment in debentures issued by, or on behalf of, any company or corporation both the`
  line `principal whereof and the interest whereon are fully and unconditionally guaranteed by the Central`
  line `Government or by a State Government;`
  line `( vii ) investment or deposit in any 1 [public sector company]:`
  line `2 [Provided that where an investment or deposit in any public sector company has been made and`
  line `such public sector company ceases to be a public sector company, —`
  line `( A ) such investment made in the shares of such company shall be deemed to be an investment`
  line `made under this clause for a period of three years from the date on which such public sector`
  line `company ceases to be a public sector company;`
  line `( B ) such other investment or deposit shall be deemed to be an investment or deposit made`
  line `under this clause for the period up to the date on which such investment or deposit becomes`
  line `repayable by such company;]`
  line `( viii ) deposits with or investment in any bonds issued by a financial corporation which is engaged`
  line `in providing long-term finance for industrial development in India and 3 [which is eligible for`
  line `deduction under clause ( viii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 36];`
  line `( ix ) deposits with or investment in any bonds issued by a public company formed and registered`
  line `in India with the main object of carrying on the business of providing long-term finance for`
  line `construction or purchase of houses in India for residential purposes and 3 [which is eligible for`
  line `deduction under clause ( viii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 36];`
  line `4 [( ixa ) deposits with or investment in any bonds issued by a public company formed and`
  line `registered in India with the main object of carrying on the business of providing long-term finance for`
  line `urban infrastructure in India.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( a ) “long - term finance” means any loan or a dvance where the terms under which moneys are`
  line `loaned or advanced provide for repayment along with interest thereof during a period of not less`
  line `than five years;`
  line `( b ) “public company” shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 3 of the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line `( c ) “urban infrastructure” means a project for providing potable water supply, sanitation and`
  line `sewerage, drainage, solid waste management, roads, bridges and flyovers or urban transport;]`
  line `( x ) investment in immovable property.`
  line `Explanation. —”Immovable property” does not include any machinery or plant (other than`
  line `machinery or plant installed in a building for the convenient occupation of the building) even though`
  line `attached to, or permanently fastened to, anything attached to the earth;]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 5, for “Government company as defined i n section 617 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of`
  line `1956)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for “which is approved by the Central Government of the purposes of clause ( viii ) of sub-section ( 10 )`
  line `of s ection 36” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2001).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
