  title `Page 129`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  sourcePage 129
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line 129
  line `1 [( xi ) deposits with the Industrial Development Bank of India established under the Industrial`
  line `Development Bank of India Act, 1964 (18 of 1964);]`
  line `2 [( xii ) any other form or mode of investment or deposit as may be prescribed.]`
  line `3 [( 6 ) In this section where any income is required to be applied or accumulated or set apart for`
  line `application, then, for such purposes the income shall be determined without any deduction or allowance`
  line `by way of depreciation or otherwise in respect of any asset, acquisition of which has been claimed as an`
  line `application of income under this section in the same or any other previous year.`
  line `( 7 ) Where a trust or an institution has been granted registration under clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 12AA or has obtained registration at any time under section 12A [as it stood before its amendment`
  line `by the Finance (No. 2) Act, 1996 (33 of 1996)] and the said registration is in force for any previous year,`
  line `then, nothing contained in section 10 [other than clause ( 1 ) and clause ( 23C ) thereof] shall operate to`
  line `exclude any income derived from the property held under trust from the total income of the person in`
  line `receipt thereof for that previous year.]`
  line `4 [12. Income of trusts or institutions from contributions. — 5 [( 1 )] Any voluntary contributions`
  line `received by a trust created wholly for charitable or religious purposes or by an institution established`
  line `wholly for such purposes (not being contributions made with a specific direction that they shall form part`
  line `of the corpus of the trust or institution) shall for the purposes of section 11 be deemed to be income`
  line `derived from property held under trust wholly for charitable or religious purposes and the provisions of`
  line `that section and section 13 shall apply accordingly.]`
  line `6 [( 2 ) The value of any services, being medical or educational services, made available by any`
  line `charitable or religious trust running a hospital or medical institution or an educational institution, to any`
  line `person referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ) or clause ( cc ) or clause ( d ) of sub-section ( 3 )`
  line `of section 13, shall be deemed to be income of such trust or institution derived from property held under`
  line `trust wholly for charitable or religious purposes during the previous year in which such services are so`
  line `provided and shall be chargeable to income-tax notwithstanding the provisions of sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 11.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- section, the expression “value” shall be the value of any`
  line `benefit or facility granted or provided free of cost or at concessional rate to any person referred to in`
  line `clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ) or clause ( cc ) or clause ( d ) of sub-section ( 3 ) of section 13.]`
  line `7 [( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 11, any amount of donation received by the trust`
  line `or institution in terms of clause ( d ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 80G 8 [in respect of which accounts of`
  line `income and expenditure have not been rendered to the authority prescribed under clause ( v ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 5C ) of that section, in the manner specified in that clause, or] which has been utilised for`
  line `purposes other than providing relief to the victims of earthquake in Gujarat or which remains unutilised in`
  line `terms of sub-section ( 5C ) of section 80G and not transferred to the Prime Minister's National Relief Fund`
  line `on or before the 31st day of March, 9 [2004] shall be deemed to be the income of the previous year and`
  line `shall accordingly be charged to tax.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `4. Sections 12 and 12A restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier section 12 was omitted by Act 4 of 1988,`
  line `s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Section 12 renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) therof by Act 10 of 2000, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `6. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 4 of 2001, s. 5 (w.e.f. 3-2-2001).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 8 (w.e.f. 3-2-2001).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 11, for the figures “2003” (w.e.f. 3 -2-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-130
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 130
  title `Page 130`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  sourcePage 130
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line 130
  line `12A. 1 [ Conditions for applicability of sections 11 and 12.] — 2 [( 1 )] The provisions of section`
  line `11 and section 12 shall not apply in relation to the income of any trust or institution unless the following`
  line `conditions are fulfilled, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the person in receipt of the income has made an application for registration of the trust or`
  line `institution in the prescribed form and in the prescribed manner to the 3 *** 4 [Principal Commissioner`
  line `or Commissioner] before the 1st day of July, 1973, or before the expiry of a period of one year from`
  line `the date of the creation of the trust or the establishment of the institution, 5 [whichever is later and`
  line `such trust or institution is registered under section 12AA]:`
  line `6 [Provided that where an application for registration of the trust or institution is made after the`
  line `expiry of the period aforesaid, the provisions of section 11 and 12 shall apply in relation to the`
  line `income of such trust or institution, —`
  line `( i ) from the date of the creation of the trust or the establishment of the institution if the 3 ***`
  line `4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] is, for reasons to be recorded in writing, satisfied`
  line `that the person in receipt of the income was prevented from making the application before the`
  line `expiry of the period aforesaid for sufficient reasons;`
  line `( ii ) from the 1st day of the financial year in which the application is made, if the`
  line `3 *** 4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] is not so satisfied:]`
  line `7 [Provided further that the provisions of this clause shall not apply in relation to any application`
  line `made on or after the 1st day of June, 2007;]`
  line `7 [( aa ) the person in receipt of the income has made an application for registration of the trust or`
  line `institution on or after the 1st day of June, 2007 in the prescribed form and manner to the 4 [Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner] and such trust or institution is registered under section 12AA;]`
  line `8 [( ab ) the person in receipt of the income has made an application for registration of the trust or`
  line `institution, in a case where a trust or an institution has been granted registration under section 12AA or`
  line `has obtained registration at any time under section 12A [as it stood before its amendment by the Finance`
  line `(No. 2) Act, 1996 (33 of 1996)], and, subsequently, it has adopted or undertaken modifications of the`
  line `objects which do not conform to the conditions of registration, in the prescribed form and manner,`
  line `within a period of thirty days from the date of said adoption or modification, to the Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner and such trust or institution is registered under section 12AA;]`
  line `( b ) where the total income of the trust or institution as computed under this Act without giving`
  line `effect to the 9 [provisions of section 11 and section 12 exceeds the maximum amount which is not`
  line `chargeable to income-tax in any previous year], the accounts of the trust or institution for that year`
  line `have been audited by an accountant as defined in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section`
  line `288 and the person in receipt of the income furnishes along with the return of income for the relevant`
  line `assessment year the report of such audit in the prescribed form duly signed and verified by such`
  line `accountant and setting forth such particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 8, for “Conditions as to registration of trusts, etc.” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2007).`
  line `2. Section 12A renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by s. 8 ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `3. The words “chief commissioner or” omitted by Act 27 of 1999, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1 -6-1999).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 5, for “whichever is later” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1997).`
  line `6. The proviso substituted by Act 49 of 1991, s. 7, (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `9. Subs by Act 29 of 2006, s. 4, for certain words and figures (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-131
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 131
  title `Page 131`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  sourcePage 131
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line 131
  line `1 [( ba ) the person in receipt of the income has furnished the return of income for the previous year`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of sub-section ( 4A ) of section 139, within the time allowed under`
  line `that section;]`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `3 [( 2 ) Where an application has been made on or after the 1st day of June, 2007, the provisions of`
  line `sections 11 and 12 shall apply in relation to the income of such trust or institution from the assessment`
  line `year immediately following the financial year in which such application is made:]`
  line `4 [Provided that where registration has been granted to the trust or institution under section 12AA,`
  line `then, the provisions of sections 11 and 12 shall apply in respect of any income derived from property held`
  line `under trust of any assessment year preceding the aforesaid assessment year, for which assessment`
  line `proceedings are pending before the Assessing Officer as on the date of such registration and the objects`
  line `and activities of such trust or institution remain the same for such preceding assessment year:`
  line `Provided further that no action under section 147 shall be taken by the Assessing Officer in case of`
  line `such trust or institution for any assessment year preceding the aforesaid assessment year only for non-`
  line `registration of such trust or institution for the said assessment year:`
  line `Provided also that provisions contained in the first and second proviso shall not apply in case of any`
  line `trust or institution which was refused registration or the registration granted to it was cancelled at any`
  line `time under section 12AA.]`
  line `5 [12AA. Procedure for registration. — ( 1 ) The 6 *** 7 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner],`
  line `on receipt of an application for registration of a trust or institution made under clause ( a ) 8 [or clause ( aa )`
  line `9 [or clause ( ab )] of sub-section ( 1 )] of section 12A, shall —`
  line `( a ) call for such documents or information from the trust or institution as he thinks necessary in`
  line `order to satisfy himself about the genuineness of activities of the trust or institution and may also`
  line `make such inquiries as he may deem necessary in this behalf; and`
  line `( b ) after satisfying himself about the objects of the trust or institution and the genuineness of its`
  line `activities, he —`
  line `( i ) shall pass an order in writing registering the trust or institution;`
  line `( ii ) shall, if he is not so satisfied, pass an order in writing refusing to register the trust or`
  line institution,
  line `and a copy of such order shall be sent to the applicant:`
  line `Provided that no order under sub-clause ( ii ) shall be passed unless the applicant has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `2. Clause ( c ) omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-1997).`
  line `6. The words “chief commissioner or” omitted by Act 27 of 1999, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1 -6-1999).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013)`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
