  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  sourcePage 135
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line 135
  line `( b ) if any land, building or other property of the trust or institution is, or continues to be, made`
  line `available for the use of any person referred to in sub-section ( 3 ), for any period during the previous`
  line `year without charging adequate rent or other compensation;`
  line `( c ) if any amount is paid by way of salary, allowance or otherwise during the previous year to any`
  line `person referred to in sub-section ( 3 ) out of the resources of the trust or institution for services`
  line `rendered by that person to such trust or institution and the amount so paid is in excess of what may be`
  line `reasonably paid for such services;`
  line `( d ) if the services of the trust or institution are made available to any person referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ) during the previous year without adequate remuneration or other compensation;`
  line `( e ) if any share, security or other property is purchased by or on behalf of the trust or institution`
  line `from any person referred to in sub-section ( 3 ) during the previous year for consideration which is`
  line `more than adequate;`
  line `( f ) if any share, security or other property is sold by or on behalf of the trust or institution to any`
  line `person referred to in sub-section ( 3 ) during the previous year for consideration which is less than`
  line adequate;
  line `1 [( g ) if any income or property of the trust or institution is diverted during the previous year in`
  line `favour of any person referred to in sub-section ( 3 ):`
  line `Provided that this clause shall not apply where the income, or the value of the property or, as the`
  line `case may be, the aggregate of the income and the value of the property, so diverted does not exceed`
  line `one thousand rupees;]`
  line `( h ) if any funds of the trust or institution are, or continue to remain, invested for any period`
  line `during the previous year (not being a period before the 1st day of January, 1971), in any concern in`
  line `which any person referred to in sub-section ( 3 ) has a substantial interest.`
  line `( 3 ) The persons referred to in clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 1 ) and sub-section ( 2 ) are the following,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( a ) the author of the trust or the founder of the institution;`
  line `2 [( b ) any person who has made a substantial contribution to the trust or institution, that is to say,`
  line `any person whose total contribution up to the end of the relevant previous year exceeds 3 [fifty`
  line `thousand] rupees];`
  line `( c ) where such author, founder or person is a Hindu undivided family, a member of the family;`
  line `4 [( cc ) any trustee of the trust or manager (by whatever name called) of the institution;]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 7, for clause ( g ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 5, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1977).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 9, for “twenty - five thousand” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1995).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-136
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 136
  title `Page 136`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  sourcePage 136
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line 136
  line `( d ) any relative of any such author, founder, person, 1 [member, trustee or manager] as aforesaid;`
  line `( e ) any concern in which any of the persons referred to in clauses ( a ), ( b ), 2 [( c ), ( cc )] and ( d ) has a`
  line `substantial interest.`
  line `( 4 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 1 ) 3 [but without prejudice to the`
  line `provisions contained in clause ( d ) of that sub-section, in a case where] the aggregate of the funds of the`
  line `trust or institution invested in a concern in which any person referred to in sub-section ( 3 ) has a`
  line `substantial interest, does not exceed five per cent. of the capital of that concern, the exemption under`
  line `4 [section 11 or section 12] shall not be denied in relation to any income other than the income arising to`
  line `the trust or the institution from such investment, by reason only that the 5 [funds of the trust or the`
  line `institution] have been invested in a concern in which such person has a substantial interest.`
  line `6 [( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in clause ( d ) of sub-section ( 1 ), where any assets (being`
  line `debentures issued by, or on behalf of, any company or corporation) are acquired by the trust or institution`
  line `after the 28th day of February, 1983 but before the 25th day of July, 1991, the exemption under`
  line `section 11 or section 12 shall not be denied in relation to any income other than the income arising to the`
  line `trust or the institution from such assets, by reason only that the funds of the trust or the institution have`
  line `been invested in such assets if such funds do not continue to remain so invested in such assets after the`
  line `31st day of March, 1992.]`
  line `7 [( 6 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ), but without prejudice`
  line `to the provisions contained in sub-section ( 2 ) of section 12, in the case of a charitable or religious trust`
  line `running an educational institution or a medical institution or a hospital, the exemption under section 11 or`
  line `section 12 shall not be denied in relation to any income, other than the income referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 12, by reason only that such trust has provided educational or medical facilities`
  line `to persons referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ) or clause ( cc ) or clause ( d ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ).]`
  line `8 [( 7 ) Nothing contained in section 11 or section 12 shall operate so as to exclude from the total`
  line `income of the previous year of the person in receipt thereof, any anonymous donation referred to in`
  line `section 115BBC on which tax is payable in accordance with the provisions of that section.]`
  line `9 [( 8 ) Nothing contained in section 11 or section 12 shall operate so as to exclude any income from the`
  line `total income of the previous year of the person in receipt thereof if the provisions of the first proviso to`
  line `clause ( 15 ) of section 2 become applicable in the case of such person in the said previous year.]`
  line `10 [( 9 ) Nothing contained in sub-section ( 2 ) of section 11 shall operate so as to exclude any income`
  line `from the total income of the previous year of a person in receipt thereof, if —`
  line `( i ) the statement referred to in clause ( a ) of the said sub-section in respect of such income is not`
  line `furnished on or before the due date specified under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139 for furnishing the`
  line `return of income for the previous year; or`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 7, for “or member” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1973).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for “( c )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1973).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 11 of 1983, s. 7, f or “, in a case where” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1983).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 7, for “section 11” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1973).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 32 of 1971, s. 6, for “money of the trust or the institution” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1971).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-1983).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-137
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 137
  title `Page 137`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  sourcePage 137
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line 137
  line `( ii ) the return of income for the previous year is not furnished by such person on or before the due`
  line `date specified under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139 for furnishing the return of income for the said`
  line `previous year.]`
  line `1 [ Explanation 1. — For the purposes of sections 11, 12, 12A and this section, “trust” includes any`
  line `other legal obligation and for the purposes of this section “relative”, in relation to an individual, means —`
  line `( i ) spouse of the individual;`
  line `( ii ) brother or sister of the individual;`
  line `( iii ) brother or sister of the spouse of the individual;`
  line `( iv ) any lineal ascendant or descendant of the individual;`
  line `( v ) any lineal ascendant or descendant of the spouse of the individual;`
  line `( vi ) spouse of a person referred to in sub-clause ( ii ), sub-clause ( iii ), sub-clause ( iv ) or`
  line `sub-clause ( v );`
  line `( vii ) any lineal descendant of a brother or sister of either the individual or of the spouse of the`
  line individual.]
  line `Explanation 2. — A trust or institution created or established for the benefit of Scheduled Castes,`
  line `backward classes, Scheduled Tribes or women and children shall not be deemed to be a trust or institution`
  line `created or established for the benefit of a religious community or caste within the meaning of clause ( b )`
  line `of sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `Explanation 3. — For the purposes of this section, a person shall be deemed to have a substantial`
  line `interest in a concern, —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the concern is a company, if its shares (not being shares entitled to a fixed rate`
  line `of dividend whether with or without a further right to participate in profits) carrying not less than`
  line `twenty per cent. of the voting power are, at any time during the previous year, owned beneficially by`
  line `such person or partly by such person and partly by one or more of the other persons referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 3 );`
  line `( ii ) in the case of any other concern, if such person is entitled, or such person and one or more of`
  line `the other persons referred to in sub-section ( 3 ) are entitled in the aggregate, at any time during the`
  line `previous year, to not less than twenty per cent. of the profits of such concern.]`
  line `2 [ 13A. Special provision relating to incomes of political parties. — Any income of a political party`
  line `which is chargeable under the head 3 *** “Income from house property” or “Income from other sources”`
  line `or 4 [Capital gains or] any income by way of voluntary contributions received by a political party from any`
  line `person shall not be included in the total income of the previous year of such political party:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 7, for Explanation 1 (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 29 of 1978, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1979).`
  line `3. The words “Interest on securities” omitted by Act 26 of 1988, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-1979).`
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-138
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 138
  title `Page 138`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  sourcePage 138
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line 138
  line `Provided that —`
  line `( a ) such political party keeps and maintains such books of account and other documents as would`
  line `enable the 1 [Assessing Officer] to properly deduce its income therefrom;`
  line `( b ) in respect of each such voluntary contribution 2 [other than contribution by way of electoral`
  line `bond] in excess of 3 [twenty thousand rupees], such political party keeps and maintains a record of`
  line `such contribution and the name and address of the person who has made such contribution; 4 ***`
  line `( c ) the accounts of such political party are audited by an accountant as defined in`
  line `the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288 2 [; and]`
  line `2 [( d ) no donation exceeding two thousand rupees is received by such political party otherwise`
  line `than by an account payee cheque drawn on a bank or an account payee bank draft or use of electronic`
  line `clearing system through a bank account or through electoral bond.`
  line `Explanation. ––For the purposes of this proviso, “electoral bond” means a bond referred to in the`
  line `Explanation to sub-section ( 3 ) of section 31 of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934):]`
  line `5 [Provided further that if the treasurer of such political party or any other person authorised by that`
  line `political party in this behalf fails to submit a report under sub-section ( 3 ) of section 29C of the`
  line `Representation of the People Act, 1951 (43 of 1951) for a financial year, no exemption under this section`
  line `shall be available for that political party for such financial year:]`
  line `2 [Provided also that such political party furnishes a return of income for the previous year in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of sub-section ( 4B ) of section 139 on or before the due date under that`
  line section.]
  line `6 [ Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, “political party” means a political party registered`
  line `under section 29A of the Representation of the People Act, 1951 (43 of 1951).]`
  line `7 [ 13B. Special provisions relating to voluntary contributions received by electoral trust. — Any`
  line `voluntary contributions received by an electoral trust shall not be included in the total income of the`
  line `previous year of such electoral trust, if —`
  line `( a ) such electoral trust distributes to any political party, registered under section 29A of the`
  line `Representation of the People Act, 1951 (43 of 1951), during the said previous year, ninety-five`
  line `per cent. of the aggregate donations received by it during the said previous year along with the`
  line `surplus, if any, brought forward from any earlier previous year; and`
  line `( b ) such electoral trust functions in accordance with the rules made by the Central Government.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 46 of 2003, s. 8, for “ten thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 11 -9-2003).`
  line `4. The word “and” omitted by Act 7 of 2017, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1 -4-2018).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 46 of 2003, s. 8 (w.e.f. 11-9-2003).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for the Explanation (w.e.f. 11-9-2003).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
