obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line 139
  line `CHAPTER IV`
  line `C OMPUTATION OF TOTAL INCOME`
  line `Heads of income`
  line `14. Heads of income. — Save as otherwise provided by this Act, all income shall, for the purposes of`
  line `charge of income-tax and computation of total income, be classified under the following heads of`
  line `income: —`
  line `A. — Salaries.`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `C. — Income from house property.`
  line `D. — Profits and gains of business or profession.`
  line `E. — Capital gains.`
  line `F. — Income from other sources.`
  line `2 [ 14A. Expenditure incurred in relation to income not includible in total income. — 3 [( 1 )] For the`
  line `purposes of computing the total income under this Chapter, no deduction shall be allowed in respect of`
  line `expenditure incurred by the assessee in relation to income which does not form part of the total income`
  line `under this Act.]`
  line `4 [( 2 ) The Assessing Officer shall determine the amount of expenditure incurred in relation to such`
  line `income which does not form part of the total income under this Act in accordance with such method as`
  line `may be prescribed, if the Assessing Officer, having regard to the accounts of the assessee, is not satisfied`
  line `with the correctness of the claim of the assessee in respect of such expenditure in relation to income`
  line `which does not form part of the total income under this Act.`
  line `( 3 ) The provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) shall also apply in relation to a case where an assessee claims`
  line `that no expenditure has been incurred by him in relation to income which does not form part of the total`
  line `income under this Act:]`
  line `5 [Provided that nothing contained in this section shall empower the Assessing Officer either to`
  line `reassess undersection 147 or pass an order enhancing the assessment or reducing a refund already made`
  line `or otherwise increasing the liability of the assessee undersection 154, for any assessment year beginning`
  line `on or before the 1st day of April, 2001.]`
  line `A. — Salaries`
  line `15. Salaries. — The following income shall be chargeable to income- tax under the head “Salaries”—`
  line `( a ) any salary due from an employer or a former employer to an assessee in the previous year,`
  line `whether paid or not;`
  line `( b ) any salary paid or allowed to him in the previous year by or on behalf of an employer or a`
  line `former employer though not due or before it became due to him;`
  line `1. The letter or words “ B. — Interest on securities ” omitted by Act 26 of 1988, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `3. Section 14A renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 21 of 2006, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 10 (w.e.f. 11-5-2001).`
