obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line 140
  line `( c ) any arrears of salary paid or allowed to him in the previous year by or on behalf of an`
  line `employer or a former employer, if not charged to income-tax for any earlier previous year.`
  line `Explanation 1 [1.] — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that where any salary paid in`
  line `advance is included in the total income of any person for any previous year it shall not be included again`
  line `in the total income of the person when the salary becomes due.`
  line `2 [ Explanation 2. — Any salary, bonus, commission or remuneration, by whatever name called, due to,`
  line `or received by, a partner of a firm from the firm shall not be rega rded as “salary” for the purposes of this`
  line section.]
  line `16. Deductions from salaries. —The income chargeable under the head “Salaries” shall be computed`
  line `after making the following deductions, namely: —`
  line `3 [ 4 * * * * *`
  line `5 [( ia ) a deduction of 6 [fifty thousand] rupees or the amount of the salary, whichever is less;]`
  line `( ii ) a deduction in respect of any allowance in the nature of an entertainment allowance`
  line `specifically granted by an employer to the assessee who is in receipt of a salary from the Government,`
  line `a sum equal to one-fifth of his salary (exclusive of any allowance, benefit or other perquisite) or five`
  line `thousand rupees, whichever is less;]`
  line `7 [( iii ) a deduction of any sum paid by the assessee on account of a tax on employment within the`
  line `meaning of clause (2) of article 276 of the Constitution, leviable by or under any law.]`
  line `8 * * * * *`
  line `17. “Salary”, “perquisite” and “profits in lieu of salary” defined. — For the purposes of`
  line `sections 15 and 16 and of this section, —`
  line `( 1 ) “salary” includes—`
  line `( i ) wages;`
  line `( ii ) any annuity or pension;`
  line `( iii ) any gratuity;`
  line `( iv ) any fees, commissions, perquisites or profits in lieu of or in addition to any salary or`
  line wages;
  line `( v ) any advance of salary;`
  line `9 [( va ) any payment received by an employee in respect of any period of leave not availed of`
  line `by him;]`
  line `( vi ) the annual accretion to the balance at the credit of an employee participating in a`
  line `recognised provident fund, to the extent to which it is chargeable to tax under rule 6 of Part A of`
  line `the Fourth Schedule;`
  line `( vii ) the aggregate of all sums that are comprised in the transferred balance as referred to in`
  line `sub-rule (2) of rule 11 of Part A of the Fourth Schedule of an employee participating in a`
  line `recognised provident fund, to the extent to which it is chargeable to tax under sub-rule (4)`
  line `thereof; and`
  line `1. Explanation renumbered as Explanation 1 thereof by Act 18 of 1992, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1993). Earlier inserted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989) and later omitted by`
  line `Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 12, for clause ( i ) and ( ii ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `4. Clause ( i ) omitted by Act 18 of 2005, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 3, for “forty thousand” (w.e.f. 1-4-2020).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 13 of 1989, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1990). Earlier clause ( iii ) omitted by Act 20 of 1974, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1975).`
  line `8. Clause ( iv ) and ( v ) omitted by Act 20 of 1974, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1975).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-1978).`
