obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line 141
  line `1 [( viii ) the contribution made by the 2 [Central Government or any other employer] in the`
  line `previous year, to the account of an employee under a pension scheme referred to insection`
  line 80CCD;]
  line `( 2 ) “perquisite” includes—`
  line `( i ) the value of rent-free accommodation provided to the assessee by his employer;`
  line `( ii ) the value of any concession in the matter of rent respecting any accommodation provided`
  line `to the assessee by his employer;`
  line `3 [ Explanation 1. — For the purposes of this sub-clause, concession in the matter of rent shall`
  line `be deemed to have been provided if, —`
  line `4 [( a ) in a case where an unfurnished accommodation is provided by any employer other`
  line `than the Central Government or any State Government and —`
  line `( i ) the accommodation is owned by the employer, the value of the accommodation`
  line `determined at the specified rate in respect of the period during which the said`
  line `accommodation was occupied by the assessee during the previous year, exceeds the rent`
  line `recoverable from, or payable by, the assessee;`
  line `( ii ) the accommodation is taken on lease or rent by the employer, the value of the`
  line `accommodation being the actual amount of lease rental paid or payable by the employer`
  line `or fifteen per cent. of salary, whichever is lower, in respect of the period during which the`
  line `said accommodation was occupied by the assessee during the previous year, exceeds the`
  line `rent recoverable from, or payable by, the assessee;]`
  line `( b ) in a case where a furnished accommodation is provided by the Central Government or`
  line `any State Government, the licence fee determined by the Central Government or any State`
  line `Government in respect of the accommodation in accordance with the rules framed by such`
  line `Government as increased by the value of furniture and fixtures in respect of the period during`
  line `which the said accommodation was occupied by the assessee during the previous year,`
  line `exceeds the aggregate of the rent re-coverable from, or payable by, the assessee and any`
  line `charges paid or payable for the furniture and fixtures by the assessee;`
  line `( c ) in a case where a furnished accommodation is provided by an employer other than the`
  line `Central Government or any State Government and —`
  line `( i ) the accommodation is owned by the employer, the value of the accommodation`
  line `determined under sub-clause ( i ) of clause ( a ) as increased by the value of the furniture`
  line `and fixtures in respect of the period during which the said accommodation was occupied`
  line `by the assessee during the previous year, exceeds the rent recoverable from, or payable`
  line `by, the assessee;`
  line `( ii ) the accommodation is taken on lease or rent by the employer, the value of the`
  line `accommodation determined under sub-clause ( ii ) of clause ( a ) as increased by the value`
  line `of the furniture and fixtures in respect of the period during which the said`
  line `accommodation was occupied by the assessee during the previous year, exceeds the rent`
  line `recoverable from, or payable by, the assessee;`
  line `( d ) in a case where the accommodation is provided by the employer in a hotel (except`
  line `where the assessee is provided such accommodation for a period not exceeding in`
  line `aggregatefifteen days on his transfer from one place to another), the value of the`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 11, for “Central Government” (w.r.e.f. 1 -4-2004).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 11, ibid. (w.r.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for clause ( a ) (w.r.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
