obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line 142
  line `accommodation determined at the rate of twenty-four per cent. of salary paid or payable for`
  line `the previous year or the actual charges paid or payable to such hotel, whichever is lower, for`
  line `the period during which such accommodation is provided, exceeds the rent recoverable from,`
  line `or payable by, the assessee.`
  line `Explanation 2. — For the purposes of this sub-clause, value of furniture and fixture shall be`
  line `ten per cent. per annum of the cost of furniture (including television sets, radio sets, refrigerators,`
  line `other household appliances, air-conditioning plant or equipment or other similar appliances or`
  line `gadgets) or if such furniture is hired from a third party, the actual hire charges payable for the`
  line `same as reduced by any charges paid or payable for the same by the assessee during the previous`
  line year.
  line `Explanation 3. — For the purposes of this sub- clause, “salary” includes the pay, allowances,`
  line `bonus or commission payable monthly or otherwise or any monetary payment, by whatever name`
  line `called, from one or more employers, as the case may be, but does not include the following,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( a ) dearness allowance or dearness pay unless it enters into the computation of`
  line `superannuation or retirement benefits of the employee concerned;`
  line `( b ) employer ’ s contribution to the provident fund account of the employee;`
  line `( c ) allowances which are exempted from the payment of tax;`
  line `( d ) value of the perquisites specified in this clause;`
  line `( e ) any payment or expenditure specifically excluded under the proviso to this clause.]`
  line `1 [ Explanation 4. — For the purposes of this sub- clause, “specified rate” shall be—`
  line `( i ) fifteen per cent. of salary in cities having population exceeding twenty-five lakhs as`
  line `per 2001 census;`
  line `( ii ) ten per cent. of salary in cities having population exceeding ten lakhs but not`
  line `exceeding twenty-five lakhs as per 2001 census; and`
  line `( iii ) seven and one-half per cent. of salary in any other place;]`
  line `( iii ) the value of any benefit or amenity granted or provided free of cost or at concessional`
  line `rate in any of the following cases —`
  line `( a ) by a company to an employee who is a director thereof;`
  line `( b ) by a company to an employee being a person who has a substantial interest in the`
  line company;
  line `( c ) by any employer (including a company) to an employee to whom the provisions of`
  line `paragraphs (a) and (b) of this sub-clause do not apply and whose income 2 [under the head`
  line `“Salaries” (whether due from, or paid or allowed by, one or more employers), exclusive of`
  line `the value of all benefits or amenities not provided for by way of monetary payment, exceeds`
  line `3 [fifty thousand rupees:]]`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 1985, s. 6, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-1986).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 13, for “twenty - four thousands rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2002).`
  line `4. The proviso omitted by Act 22 of 2007, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008). Earlier the proviso inserted by Act 10 of 2000, s. 11`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
