obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line 143
  line `1 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the use of any vehicle`
  line `provided by a company or an employer for journey by the assessee from his residence to his`
  line `office or other place of work, or from such office or place to his residence, shall not be regarded`
  line `as a benefit or amenity granted or provided to him free of cost or at concessional rate for the`
  line `purposes of this sub-clause;]`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `( iv ) any sum paid by the employer in respect of any obligation which, but for such payment,`
  line `would have been payable by the assessee;`
  line `( v ) any sum payable by the employer, whether directly or through a fund, other than a`
  line `recognised provident fund or an approved superannuation fund 3 [or a Deposit-linked Insurance`
  line `Fund established under section 3G of the Coal Mines Provident Fund and Miscellaneous`
  line `Provisions Act, 1948 (46 of 1948), or, as the case may be, section 6C of the Employees ’`
  line `Provident Funds and Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1952 (19 of 1952)], to effect an assurance on`
  line `the life of the assessee or to effect a contract for an 4 [annuity;]`
  line `5 [( vi ) the value of any specified security or sweat equity shares allotted or transferred, directly`
  line `or indirectly, by the employer, or former employer, free of cost or at concessional rate to the`
  line assessee.
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-clause, —`
  line `( a ) “specified security” means the securities as defined in clause ( h ) of section 2 of the`
  line `Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956) and, where employees ’ stock option`
  line `has been granted under any plan or scheme therefor, includes the securities offered under`
  line `such plan or scheme;`
  line `( b ) “sweat equity shares” means equity shares issued by a company to its employees or`
  line `directors at a discount or for consideration other than cash for providing know-how or`
  line `making available rights in the nature of intellectual property rights or value additions, by`
  line `whatever name called;`
  line `( c ) the value of any specified security or sweat equity shares shall be the fair market`
  line `value of the specified security or sweat equity shares, as the case may be, on the date on`
  line `which the option is exercised by the assessee as reduced by the amount actually paid by, or`
  line `recovered from, the assessee in respect of such security or shares;`
  line `( d ) “fair market value” means the value determined in accordance with the method as`
  line `may be prescribed;`
  line `( e ) “option” means a right but not an obligation granted to an employee to apply for the`
  line `specified security or sweat equity shares at a predetermined price;`
  line `( vii ) the amount of any contribution to an approved superannuation fund by the employer in`
  line `respect of the assessee, to the extent it exceeds 6 [one lakh rupees]; and`
  line `( viii ) the value of any other fringe benefit or amenity as may be prescribed:]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1989, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `2. Sub-clause ( iiia ) omitted by Act 10 of 2000, s. 11 (w.e.f 1-4-2001).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 99 of 1976, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 9, for “annuity; and” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2010).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for sub-clause ( vi ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 9, for “one lakh and fifty thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
