obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line 144
  line `1 [Provided that nothing in this clause shall apply to, —`
  line `( i ) the value of any medical treatment provided to an employee or any member of his`
  line `family in any hospital maintained by the employer;`
  line `2 [( ii ) any sum paid by the employer in respect of any expenditure actually incurred by`
  line `the employee on his medical treatment or treatment of any member of his family —`
  line `( a ) in any hospital maintained by the Government or any local authority or any`
  line `other hospital approved by the Government for the purposes of medical treatment of`
  line `its employees;`
  line `( b ) in respect of the prescribed diseases or ailments, in any hospital approved by`
  line `the 3 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] having regard to the`
  line `prescribed guidelines:`
  line `Provided that, in a case falling in sub-clause (b), the employee shall attach with his`
  line `return of income a certificate from the hospital specifying the disease or ailment for`
  line `which medical treatment was required and the receipt for the amount paid to the`
  line hospital;]
  line `( iii ) any portion of the premium paid by an employer in relation to an employee, to`
  line `effect or to keep in force an insurance on the health of such employee under any scheme`
  line `approved by the Central Government 4 [or the Insurance Regulatory and Development`
  line `Authority established under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 3 of the Insurance Regulatory and`
  line `Development Authority Act, 1999 (41 of 1999),] for the purposes of clause ( ib ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 36;`
  line `( iv ) any sum paid by the employer in respect of any premium paid by the employee to`
  line `effect or to keep in force an insurance on his health or the health of any member of his`
  line `family under any scheme approved by the Central Government 4 [or the Insurance`
  line `Regulatory and Development Authority established under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 3 of`
  line `the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority Act, 1999 (41 of 1999),] for the`
  line `purposes of section 80D;`
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `( vi ) any expenditure incurred by the employer on —`
  line `( 1 ) medical treatment of the employee, or any member of the family of such`
  line `employee, outside India;`
  line `( 2 ) 6 [travel and stay] abroad of the employee or any member of the family of`
  line `such employee for medical treatment;`
  line `( 3 ) travel and stay abroad of one attendant who accompanies the patient in`
  line `connection with such treatment,`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 10, for sub-clause ( ii ) (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1993). Earlier substituted by Act 18 of 1992,`
  line `s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `5. Clause ( v ) omitted by Act 13 of 2018, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 38 of 1993, s. 8, for “travel or stay” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1993).`
