obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line 145
  line `1 [subject to the condition that —`
  line `( A ) the expenditure on medical treatment and stay abroad shall be excluded from perquisite`
  line `only to the extent permitted by the Reserve Bank of India; and`
  line `( B ) the expenditure on travel shall be excluded from perquisite only in the case of an`
  line `employee whose gross total income, as computed before including therein the said expenditure,`
  line `does not exceed two lakh rupees;]`
  line `( vii ) any sum paid by the employer in respect of any expenditure actually incurred by`
  line `the employee for any of the purposes specified in clause ( vi ) subject to the conditions`
  line `specified in or under that clause:`
  line `2 [Provided further that for the assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April,`
  line `2002, nothing contained in this clause shall apply to any employee whose income under`
  line `the head “Salaries” (whether due from, or paid or allowed by, one or more employers)`
  line `exclusive of the value of all perquisites not provided for by way of monetary payment,`
  line `does not exceed one lakh rupees.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of clause ( 2 ), —`
  line `( i ) “hospital” includes a dispensary or a clinic 3 [or a nursing home];`
  line `( ii ) “family”, in relation to an individual, shall have the same meaning as in clause ( 5 ) of`
  line `section 10; and`
  line `( iii ) “gross total income” shall have the same meaning as in clause ( 5 ) of section 80B;]`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `( 3 ) “profits in lieu of salary” includes—`
  line `( i ) the amount of any compensation due to or received by an assessee from his employer or`
  line `former employer at or in connection with the termination of his employment or the modification`
  line `of the terms and conditions relating thereto;`
  line `( ii ) any payment [other than any payment referred to in clause ( 10 ] 5 [, clause ( 10A )]`
  line `6 [, clause ( 10B )], clause ( 11 ), 7 [clause ( 12 ) 8 [, clause ( 13 )] or clause ( 13A )] of section 10], due to`
  line `or received by an assessee from an employer or a former employer or from a provident or other`
  line `fund 9 ***, to the extent to which it does not consist of contributions by the assessee or 10 [interest`
  line `on such contributions or any sum received under a Keyman insurance policy including the sum`
  line `allocated by way of bonus on such policy.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- clause, the expression “Keyman insurance policy”`
  line `shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( 10D ) of section 10;]`
  line `11 [( iii ) any amount due to or received, whether in lump sum or otherwise, by any assessee`
  line `from any person —`
  line `( A ) before his joining any employment with that person; or`
  line `( B ) after cessation of his employment with that person.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1993, s. 8, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-1993)`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 11 (w.e.f,. 1-4-2002).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `4. Sub-clause ( vi ) omitted by Act 32 of 1985, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 15 of 1965, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 25 of 1975, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 31 of 1964, s. 4, for “or clause ( 12 )” (w.e.f. 6 -10-1964).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-1996).`
  line `9. The brackets and words “(not being an approved superannuation fund)” omitted by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1996).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 8, for “interest on such contributions.” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1996).`
  line `11. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
