obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line 146
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `18. [ Interest on securities.] — Omitted by the Finance Act, 1988 (26 of 1988), s. 10 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `19. [ Deductions from interest on securities. ] — Omitted by s. 10, ibid. ( w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `20. [ Deductions from interest on securities in the case of a banking company.] — Omitted by s. 10,`
  line `ibid. ( w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `21. [ Amounts not deductible from interest on securities. ] — Omitted by s. 10, ibid. ( w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `C. — Income from house property`
  line `22. Income from house property. — The annual value of property consisting of any buildings or`
  line `lands appurtenant thereto of which the assessee is the owner, other than such portions of such property as`
  line `he may occupy for the purposes of any business or profession carried on by him the profits of which are`
  line `chargeable to income-tax, shall be chargeable to income- tax under the head “Income from house`
  line property”.
  line `2 [23. Annual value how determined. — ( 1 ) For the purposes of section 22, the annual value of any`
  line `property shall be deemed to be —`
  line `( a ) the sum for which the property might reasonably be expected to let from year to year; or`
  line `( b ) where the property or any part of the property is let and the actual rent received or receivable`
  line `by the owner in respect thereof is in excess of the sum referred to in clause ( a ), the amount so`
  line `received or receivable; or`
  line `( c ) where the property or any part of the property is let and was vacant during the whole or any`
  line `part of the previous year and owing to such vacancy the actual rent received or receivable by the`
  line `owner in respect thereof is less than the sum referred to in clause ( a ), the amount so received or`
  line `receivable:`
  line `Provided that the taxes levied by any local authority in respect of the property shall be deducted`
  line `(irrespective of the previous year in which the liability to pay such taxes was incurred by the owner`
  line `according to the method of accounting regularly employed by him) in determining the annual value of`
  line `the property of that previous year in which such taxes are actually paid by him.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of clause ( b ) or clause ( c ) of this sub-section, the amount of`
  line `actual rent received or receivable by the owner shall not include, subject to such rules as may be`
  line `made in this behalf, the amount of rent which the owner cannot realise.`
  line `( 2 ) Where the property consists of a house or part of a house which —`
  line `( a ) is in the occupation of the owner for the purposes of his own residence; or`
  line `( b ) cannot actually be occupied by the owner by reason of the fact that owing to his employment,`
  line `business or profession carried on at any other place, he has to reside at that other place in a building`
  line `not belonging to him,`
  line `the annual value of such house or part of the house shall be taken to be nil.`
  line `( 3 ) The provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) shall not apply if —`
  line `( a ) the house or part of the house is actually let during the whole or any part of the previous`
  line `year; or`
  line `( b ) any other benefit therefrom is derived by the owner.`
  line `( 4 ) Where the property referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) consists of more than 3 [two houses] —`
  line `( a ) the provisions of that sub-section shall apply only in respect of 4 [two] of such houses, which`
  line `the assessee may, at his option, specify in this behalf;`
  line `1. The heading “ B. — Interest on securities ” omitted by Act 26 of 1988, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 14, for section 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 4, for “one house” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2020).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “one” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2020).`
