obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line 147
  line `( b ) the annual value of the house or houses, 1 [other than the house or houses] in respect of which`
  line `the assessee has exercised an option under clause ( a ), shall be determined under sub-section ( 1 ) as if`
  line `such house or houses had been let.]`
  line `2 [( 5 ) Where the property consisting of any building or land appurtenant thereto is held as`
  line `stock-in-trade and the property or any part of the property is not let during the whole or any part of the`
  line `previous year, the annual value of such property or part of the property, for the period up to 3 [two years]`
  line `from the end of the financial year in which the certificate of completion of construction of the property is`
  line `obtained from the competent authority, shall be taken to be nil.]`
  line `4 [ 24. Deductions from income from house property. — Income chargeable under the he ad “Income`
  line `from house property” shall be computed after making the following deductions, namely:—`
  line `( a ) a sum equal to thirty per cent. of the annual value;`
  line `( b ) where the property has been acquired, constructed, repaired, renewed or reconstructed with`
  line `borrowed capital, the amount of any interest payable on such capital:`
  line `Provided that in respect of property referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) of section 23, the amount of`
  line `deduction 5 [or, as the case may be, the aggregate of the amount of deduction] shall not exceed thirty`
  line `thousand rupees:`
  line `Provided further that where the property referred to in the first proviso is acquired or constructed`
  line `with capital borrowed on or after the 1st day of April, 1999 and such acquisition or construction is`
  line `completed 6 [within 7 [five years] from the end of the financial year in which capital was borrowed],`
  line `the amount of deduction 5 [or, as the case may be, the aggregate of the amounts of deduction] under`
  line `this clause shall not exceed 8 [two lakh rupees].`
  line `Explanation. — Where the property has been acquired or constructed with borrowed capital, the`
  line `interest, if any, payable on such capital borrowed for the period prior to the previous year in which`
  line `the property has been acquired or constructed, as reduced by any part thereof allowed as deduction`
  line `under any other provision of this Act, shall be deducted under this clause in equal instalments for the`
  line `said previous year and for each of the four immediately succeeding previous years:]`
  line `9 [Provided also that no deduction shall be made under the second proviso unless the assessee`
  line `furnishes a certificate, from the person to whom any interest is payable on the capital borrowed,`
  line `specifying the amount of interest payable by the assessee for the purpose of such acquisition or`
  line `construction of the property, or, conversion of the whole or any part of the capital borrowed which`
  line `remains to be repaid as a new loan.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this proviso, the expression “new loan” means the whole or`
  line `any part of a loan taken by the assessee subsequent to the capital borrowed, for the purpose of`
  line `repayment of such capital.]`
  line `5 [Provided also that the aggregate of the amounts of deduction under the first and second provisos`
  line `shall not exceed two lakh rupees.]`
  line `25. Amounts not deductible from income from house property. — Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 24, any 10 *** interest chargeable under this Act which is payable outside India (not`
  line `being interest on a loan issued for public subscription before the 1st day of April, 1938), on which tax has`
  line `not been paid or deducted under Chapter XVII-B and in respect of which there is no person in India who`
  line `may be treated as an agent under section 163 shall not be deducted in computing the income chargeable`
  line `under the head “Income from house property”.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 4, for “other than the house” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2020).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018)`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 5, for “one year” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2020).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 15, for section 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2020).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 12, for “before the 1st day of April, 2003” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2003).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 10, for “ three years ” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 10, for “one lakh fifty thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2015).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `10. The words “annual charge or” omitted by Act 14 of 2001, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1 -4-2002).`
