obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line 148
  line `1 [ 25A. Special provision for arrears of rent and unrealised rent received subsequently. — ( 1 ) The`
  line `amount of arrears of rent received from a tenant or the unrealised rent realised subsequently from a`
  line `tenant, as the case may be, by an assessee shall be deemed to be the income from house property in`
  line `respect of the financial year in which such rent is received or realised, and shall be included in the total`
  line `income of the assessee under the head “Income from house property”, whether the assessee is the owner`
  line `of the property or not in that financial year.`
  line `( 2 ) A sum equal to thirty per cent. of the arrears of rent or the unrealised rent referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) shall be allowed as deduction.]`
  line `26. Property owned by co-owners. — Where property consisting of buildings or buildings and lands`
  line `appurtenant thereto is owned by two or more persons and their respective shares are definite and`
  line `ascertainable, such persons shall not in respect of such property be assessed as an association of persons,`
  line `but the share of each such person in the income from the property as computed in accordance with`
  line `sections 22 to 25 shall be included in his total income.`
  line `2 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, in applying the provisions of sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 23 for computing the share of each such person as is referred to in this section, such share shall`
  line `be computed, as if each such person is individually entitled to the relief provided in that sub-section.`
  line `27. “Owner of house property”, “annual charge”, etc., defined. — For the purposes of`
  line `sections 22 to 26 —`
  line `( i ) an individual who transfers otherwise than for adequate consideration any house property to`
  line `his or her spouse, not being a transfer in connection with an agreement to live apart, or to a minor`
  line `child not being a married daughter, shall be deemed to be the owner of the house property so`
  line transferred;
  line `( ii ) the holder of an impartible estate shall be deemed to be the individual owner of all the`
  line `properties comprised in the estate;`
  line `3 [( iii ) a member of a co-operative society, company or other association of persons to whom a`
  line `building or part thereof is allotted or leased under a house building scheme of the society, company or`
  line `association, as the case may be, shall be deemed to be the owner of that building or part thereof;`
  line `( iiia ) a person who is allowed to take or retain possession of any building or part thereof in part`
  line `performance of a contract of the nature referred to in section 53A of the Transfer of Property`
  line `Act, 1882 (4 of 1882), shall be deemed to be the owner of that building or part thereof;`
  line `( iiib ) a person who acquires any rights (excluding any rights by way of a lease from month to`
  line `month or for a period not exceeding one year) in or with respect to any building or part thereof, by`
  line `virtue of any such transaction as is referred to in clause ( f ) of section 269 UA, shall be deemed to be`
  line `the owner of that building or part thereof;]`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `( vi ) taxes levied by a local authority in respect of any property shall be deemed to include service`
  line `taxes levied by the local authority in respect of the property.`
  line `28. Profits and gains of business or profession. — The following income shall be chargeable to`
  line `income- tax under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession”,—`
  line `( i ) the profits and gains of any business or profession which was carried on by the assessee at any`
  line `time during the previous year;`
  line `( ii ) any compensation or other payment due to or received by, —`
  line `( a ) any person, by whatever name called, managing the whole or substantially the whole of`
  line `the affairs of an Indian company, at or in connection with the termination of his management or`
  line `the modification of the terms and conditions relating thereto;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 11 for sections 25A, 25AA and 25B (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 6, for clause ( iii ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `4. Clauses (i v ) and ( v ) omitted by Act 14 of 2001, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
