obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line 149
  line `( b ) any person, by whatever name called, managing the whole or substantially the whole of`
  line `the affairs in India of any other company, at or in connection with the termination of his office or`
  line `the modification of the terms and conditions relating thereto;`
  line `( c ) any person, by whatever name called, holding an agency in India for any part of the`
  line `activities relating to the business of any other person, at or in connection with the termination of`
  line `the agency or the modification of the terms and conditions relating thereto;`
  line `1 [( d ) any person, for or in connection with the vesting in the Government, or in any`
  line `corporation owned or controlled by the Government, under any law for the time being in force, of`
  line `the management of any property or business;]`
  line `2 [( e ) any person, by whatever name called, at or in connection with the termination or the`
  line `modification of the terms and conditions, of any contract relating to his business;]`
  line `( iii ) income derived by a trade, professional or similar association from specific services`
  line `performed for its members;`
  line `3 [( iiia ) profits on sale of a licence granted under the Imports (Control) Order, 1955, made under`
  line `the Imports and Exports (Control) Act, 1947 (18 of 1947);]`
  line `4 [( iiib ) cash assistance (by whatever name called) received or receivable by any person against`
  line `exports under any scheme of the Government of India;]`
  line `5 [( iiic ) any duty of customs or excise re-paid or re-payable as drawback to any person against`
  line `exports under the Customs and Central Excise Duties Drawback Rules, 1971;]`
  line `6 [( iiid ) any profit on the transfer of the Duty Entitlement Pass Book Scheme, being the Duty`
  line `Remission Scheme under the export and import policy formulated and announced under section 5 of`
  line `the Foreign Trade (Development and Regulation) Act, 1992 (22 of 1992);]`
  line `7 [( iiie ) any profit on the transfer of the Duty Free Replenishment Certificate, being the Duty`
  line `Remission Scheme under the export and import policy formulated and announced under section 5 of`
  line `the Foreign Trade (Development and Regulation) Act, 1992 (22 of 1992);]`
  line `8 [( iv ) the value of any benefit or perquisite, whether convertible into money or not, arising from`
  line `business or the exercise of a profession;]`
  line `9 [( v ) any interest, salary, bonus, commission or remuneration, by whatever name called, due to, or`
  line `received by, a partner of a firm from such firm:`
  line `Provided that where any interest, salary, bonus, commission or remuneration, by whatever name`
  line `called, or any part thereof has not been allowed to be deducted under clause ( b ) of section 40, the`
  line `income under this clause shall be adjusted to the extent of the amount not so allowed to be deducted;]`
  line `10 [( va ) any sum, whether received or receivable, in cash or kind, under an agreement for —`
  line `( a ) not carrying out any activity in relation to any business 11 [or profession]; or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1973, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1967).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 55 of 2005, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `7. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 5 of 1964, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-1964).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993). Earlier clause ( v ) was inserted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989) and`
  line `later omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `11. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017)`
