obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line 150
  line `( b ) not sharing any know-how, patent, copyright, trade-mark, licence, franchise or any other`
  line `business or commercial right of similar nature or information or technique likely to assist in the`
  line `manufacture or processing of goods or provision for services:`
  line `Provided that sub-clause ( a ) shall not apply to —`
  line `( i ) any sum, whether received or receivable, in cash or kind, on account of transfer of the`
  line `right to manufacture, produce or process any article or thing or right to carry on any`
  line `business 1 [or profession], which is charge able under the head “Capital gains”;`
  line `( ii ) any sum received as compensation, from the multi-lateral fund of the Montreal`
  line `Protocol on Substances that Deplete the Ozone layer under the United Nations Environment`
  line `Programme, in accordance with the terms of agreement entered into with the Government of`
  line India.
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( i ) “agreement” includes any arrangement or understanding or action in concert,—`
  line `( A ) whether or not such arrangement, understanding or action is formal or in writing; or`
  line `( B ) whether or not such arrangement, understanding or action is intended to be`
  line `enforceable by legal proceedings;`
  line `( ii ) “service” means service of any description which is made available to potential users and`
  line `includes the provision of services in connection with business of any industrial or commercial`
  line `nature such as accounting, banking, communication, conveying of news or information,`
  line `advertising, entertainment, amusement, education, financing, insurance, chit funds, real estate,`
  line `construction, transport, storage, processing, supply of electrical or other energy, boarding and`
  line lodging;]
  line `2 [( vi ) any sum received under a Keyman insurance policy including the sum allocated by way of`
  line `bonus on such policy.`
  line `3 [( via ) the fair market value of inventory as on the date on which it is converted into, or treated`
  line `as, a capital asset determined in the prescribed manner;]`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, the expression “Keyman insurance policy” shall`
  line `have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( 10D ) of section 10;]`
  line `4 [( vii ) any sum, whether received or receivable, in cash or kind, on account of any capital asset`
  line `(other than land or goodwill or financial instrument) being demolished, destroyed, discarded or`
  line `transferred, if the whole of the expenditure on such capital asset has been allowed as a deduction`
  line `under section 35AD.]`
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `Explanation 2. — Where speculative transactions carried on by an assessee are of such a nature as`
  line `to constitute a business, the business (hereinafter referred to as “speculation business”) shall be`
  line `deemed to be distinct and separate from any other business.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-10-1996).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `5. Explanation 1 omitted by 4 of 1988, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
