  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  sourcePage 151
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line 151
  line `29. Income from profits and gains of business or profession, how computed. — The income`
  line `referred to in section 28 shall be computed in accordance with the provisions contained in sections`
  line `30 to 1 [43D].`
  line `30. Rent, rates, taxes, repairs and insurance for buildings. — In respect of rent, rates, taxes, repairs`
  line `and insurance for premises, used for the purposes of the business or profession, the following deductions`
  line `shall be allowed —`
  line `( a ) where the premises are occupied by the assessee —`
  line `( i ) as a tenant, the rent paid for such premises; and further if he has undertaken to bear the`
  line `cost of repairs to the premises, the amount paid on account of such repairs;`
  line `( ii ) otherwise than as a tenant, the amount paid by him on account of current repairs to the`
  line premises;
  line `( b ) any sums paid on account of land revenue, local rates or municipal taxes;`
  line `( c ) the amount of any premium paid in respect of insurance against risk of damage or destruction`
  line `of the premises.`
  line `2 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the amount paid on account of`
  line `the cost of repairs referred to in sub-clause ( i ), and the amount paid on account of current repairs referred`
  line `to in sub-clause ( ii ), of clause ( a ), shall not include any expenditure in the nature of capital expenditure.]`
  line `31. Repairs and insurance of machinery, plant and furniture. — In respect of repairs and insurance`
  line `of machinery, plant or furniture used for the purposes of the business or profession, the following`
  line `deductions shall be allowed —`
  line `( i ) the amount paid on account of current repairs thereto;`
  line `( ii ) the amount of any premium paid in respect of insurance against risk of damage or destruction`
  line thereof.
  line `3 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the amount paid on account of`
  line `current repairs shall not include any expenditure in the nature of capital expenditure.]`
  line `32. Depreciation. — ( 1 ) 4 [In respect of depreciation of —`
  line `( i ) buildings, machinery, plant or furniture, being tangible assets;`
  line `( ii ) know-how, patents, copyrights, trade marks, licences, franchises or any other business or`
  line `commercial rights of similar nature, being intangible assets acquired on or after the 1st day of April,`
  line 1998,
  line `owned, wholly or partly, by the assessee and used for the purposes of the business or profession, the`
  line `following deductions shall be allowed —`
  line `5 [( i ) in the case of assets of an undertaking engaged in generation or generation and distribution`
  line `of power, such percentage on the actual cost thereof to the assessee as may be prescribed;]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 10, for “43C” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1992).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 9, for certain words and figures (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 7 of 1998, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
