obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line 153
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this proviso, —`
  line `( a ) the expression “commercial vehicle” means “heavy goods vehicle”, “heavy passenger motor`
  line `vehicle”, “light motor vehicle”, “medium goods vehicle” and “medium passenger motor vehicle” but`
  line `does not include “maxi - cab”, “motor - cab”, “tractor” and “road - roller”;`
  line `( b ) the expressions “heavy goods vehicle”, “heavy passenger motor vehicle”, “light motor`
  line `vehicle”, “medium goods vehicle”, “medium passenger motor vehicle”, “maxi - cab”, “motor - cab”,`
  line `“tractor” and “road roller” shall have the meanings respectively as assigned to them in section 2 of`
  line `the Motor Vehicles Act, 1988 (59 of 1988):]`
  line `1 [Provided also that, in respect of the previous year relevant to the assessment year commencing`
  line `on the 1st day of April, 1991, the deduction in relation to any block of assets under this clause shall,`
  line `in the case of a company, be restricted to seventy-five per cent. of the amount calculated at the`
  line `percentage, on the written down value of such assets, prescribed under this Act immediately before`
  line `the commencement of the Taxation Laws (Amendment) Act, 1991 (2 of 1991):]`
  line `2 [Provided also that the aggregate deduction, in respect of depreciation of buildings, machinery,`
  line `plant or furniture, being tangible assets or know-how, patents, copyrights, trademarks, licences,`
  line `franchises or any other business or commercial rights of similar nature, being intangible assets`
  line `allowable to the predecessor and the successor in the case of succession referred to in 3 [clause ( xiii ),`
  line `clause ( xiiib ) and clause ( xiv )] of section 47 or section 170 or to the amalgamating company and the`
  line `amalgamated company in the case of amalgamation, or to the demerged company and the resulting`
  line `company in the case of demerger, as the case may be, shall not exceed in any previous year the`
  line `deduction calculated at the prescribed rates as if the succession or the amalgamation or the demerger,`
  line `as the case may be, had not taken place, and such deduction shall be apportioned between the`
  line `predecessor and the successor, or the amalgamating company and the amalgamated company, or the`
  line `demerged company and the resulting company, as the case may be, in the ratio of the number of days`
  line `for which the assets were used by them.]`
  line `4 [ Explanation 1. — Where the business or profession of the assessee is carried on in a building not`
  line `owned by him but in respect of which the assessee holds a lease or other right of occupancy and any`
  line `capital expenditure is incurred by the assessee for the purposes of the business or profession on the`
  line `construction of any structure or doing of any work in or in relation to, and by way of renovation or`
  line `extension of, or improvement to, the building, then, the provisions of this clause shall apply as if the`
  line `said structure or work is a building owned by the assessee.`
  line `Explanation 2. — 5 [For the purposes of this sub-section] “written down value of the block of`
  line `assets” shall have the same meaning as in clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 6 ) of section 43.]`
  line `6 [ Explanation 3. — For the purposes of this sub-section, 7 [the expression “assets”] shall mean—`
  line `( a ) tangible assets, being buildings, machinery, plant or furniture;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1991, s. 4 (w.e.f. 15-1-1991). Later Act 2 of 1991 repealed by Act 23 of 2016, s. 2 and the First Schedule`
  line `(except s. 6) (w.e.f. 6-5-2016).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 12, for the fourth proviso (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 8, for “clause ( xiii ) and clause ( xiv )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2011).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 14, for “For the purposes of this clause” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2003).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 11, for ‘the expressions “assets” and “block of assets” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2010).`
