obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line 154
  line `( b ) intangible assets, being know-how, patents, copyrights, trade marks, licences, franchises`
  line `or any other business or commercial rights of similar nature.`
  line `Explanation 4. — For the purposes of this sub- section, the expression “know - how” means any`
  line `industrial information or technique likely to assist in the manufacture or processing of goods or in`
  line `the working of a mine, oil-well or other sources of mineral deposits (including searching for`
  line `discovery or testing of deposits for the winning of access thereto).]`
  line `1 [ Explanation 5. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the provisions of this`
  line `sub-section shall apply whether or not the assessee has claimed the deduction in respect of`
  line `depreciation in computing his total income;]`
  line `2 [( iia ) in the case of any new machinery or plant (other than ships and aircraft), which has been`
  line `acquired and installed after the 31st day of March, 2005, by an assessee engaged in the business of`
  line `manufacture or production of any article or thing 3 [ 4 [or in the business of generation, transmission or`
  line `distribution] of power], a further sum equal to twenty per cent. of the actual cost of such machinery or`
  line `plant shall be allowed as deduction under clause ( ii ):`
  line `5 [Provided that where an assessee, sets up an undertaking or enterprise for manufacture or`
  line `production of any article or thing, on or after the 1st day of April, 2015 in any backward area notified`
  line `by the Central Government in this behalf, in the State of Andhra Pradesh or in the State of Bihar or in`
  line `the State of Telangana or in the State of West Bengal, and acquires and installs any new machinery or`
  line `plant (other than ships and aircraft) for the purposes of the said undertaking or enterprise during the`
  line `period beginning on the 1st day of April, 2015 and ending before the 1st day of April, 2020 in the`
  line `said backward area, then, the provisions of clause ( iia ) s hall have effect, as if for the words “twenty`
  line `per cent. ”, the words “thirty -five per cent. ” had been substituted: ]`
  line `6 [Provided further] that no deduction shall be allowed in respect of —`
  line `( A ) any machinery or plant which, before its installation by the assessee, was used either`
  line `within or outside India by any other person; or`
  line `( B ) any machinery or plant installed in any office premises or any residential accommodation,`
  line `including accommodation in the nature of a guest-house; or`
  line `( C ) any office appliances or road transport vehicles; or`
  line `( D ) any machinery or plant, the whole of the actual cost of which is allowed as a deduction`
  line `(whether by way of depreciation or otherwise) in computing the income chargeable under the`
  line `head “Profits and gains of business or profession” of any one previous year;]`
  line `7 [( iii ) in the case of any building, machinery, plant or furniture in respect of which depreciation is`
  line `claimed and allowed under clause ( i ) and which is sold, discarded, demolished or destroyed in the`
  line `previous year (other than the previous year in which it is first brought into use), the amount by which`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 8, for clause ( iia ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 13, for “or in the business of generation or generation and distribution” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for “Provided” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2016).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
