obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line 155
  line `the moneys payable in respect of such building, machinery, plant or furniture, together with the`
  line `amount of scrap value, if any, fall short of the written down value thereof:`
  line `Provided that such deficiency is actually written off in the books of the assessee.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( 1 ) “moneys payable” in respect of any b uilding, machinery, plant or furniture includes —`
  line `( a ) any insurance, salvage or compensation moneys payable in respect thereof;`
  line `( b ) where the building, machinery, plant or furniture is sold, the price for which it is sold,`
  line `so, however, that where the actual cost of a motor car is, in accordance with the proviso to`
  line `clause ( 1 ) of section 43, taken to be twenty-five thousand rupees, the moneys payable in respect`
  line `of such motor car shall be taken to be a sum which bears to the amount for which the motor car is`
  line `sold or, as the case may be, the amount of any insurance, salvage or compensation moneys`
  line `payable in respect thereof (including the amount of scrap value, if any) the same proportion as the`
  line `amount of twenty-five thousand rupees bears to the actual cost of the motor car to the assessee as`
  line `it would have been computed before applying the said proviso;`
  line `( 2 ) “sold” includes a transfer by way of exchange or a compulsory acquisition under any law`
  line `for the time being in force but does not include a transfer, in a scheme of amalgamation, of any`
  line `asset by the amalgamating company to the amalgamated company where the amalgamated`
  line `company is 1 [an Indian company or in a scheme of amalgamation of a banking company, as`
  line `referred to in clause ( c ) of section 5 of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949) with a`
  line `banking institution as referred to in sub-section ( 15 ) of section 45 of the said Act, sanctioned and`
  line `brought into force by the Central Government under sub-section ( 7 ) of section 45 of that Act of`
  line `any asset by the banking company to the banking institution].]`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 [( 2 ) Where, in the assessment of the assessee, full effect cannot be given to any allowance under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) in any previous year, owing to there being no profits or gains chargeable for that previous`
  line `year, or owing to the profits or gains chargeable being less than the allowance, then, subject to the`
  line `provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 72 and sub-section ( 3 ) of section 73, the allowance or the part of`
  line `the allowance to which effect has not been given, as the case may be, shall be added to the amount of the`
  line `allowance for depreciation for the following previous year and deemed to be part of that allowance, or if`
  line `there is no such allowance for that previous year, be deemed to be the allowance for that previous year,`
  line `and so on for the succeeding previous years.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 8, for “an Indian Company” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2005).`
  line `2. Clauses ( iv ), ( v ) and ( vi ) omitted by Act 46 of 1986, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs-section ( 1A ) omitted by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 21, for sub-section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
