obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line 161
  line `machinery or plant of the nature referred to in clauses ( a ), ( b ) and ( d ) of 1 [the second proviso]`
  line `to sub-section ( 1 )] for the purposes of the business of the undertaking; or`
  line `( c ) if at any time before the expiry of the ten years aforesaid, the assesseeutilises the`
  line `amount credited to the reserve account under sub-section ( 4 ) for distribution by way of`
  line `dividends or profits or for remittance outside India as profits or for the creation of any assets`
  line `outside India or for any other purpose which is not a purpose of the business of the`
  line undertaking,
  line `and the provisions of sub-section ( 4A ) of section 155 shall apply accordingly:`
  line `Provided that nothing in clause ( a ) shall apply —`
  line `( i ) where the ship, aircraft, machinery or plant is sold or otherwise transferred by the assessee`
  line `to the Government, a local authority, a corporation established by a Central, State or Provincial`
  line `Act or a Government company as defined in section 617 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line or
  line `( ii ) where the sale or transfer of the ship, aircraft, machinery or plant is made in connection`
  line `with the amalgamation or succession, referred to in sub-section ( 6 ) or sub-section ( 7 ).`
  line `( 6 ) Where, in a scheme of amalgamation, the amalgamating company sells or otherwise`
  line `transfers to the amalgamated company any ship, aircraft, machinery or plant, in respect of which`
  line `investment allowance has been allowed to the amalgamating company under sub-section ( 1 ), —`
  line `( a ) the amalgamated company shall continue to fulfil the conditions mentioned in`
  line `sub-section ( 4 ) in respect of the reserve created by the amalgamating company and in respect`
  line `of the period within which such ship, aircraft, machinery or plant shall not be sold or`
  line `otherwise transferred and in default of any of these conditions, the provisions of`
  line `sub-section ( 4A ) of section 155 shall apply to the amalgamated company as they would have`
  line `applied to the amalgamating company had it committed the default; and`
  line `( b ) the balance of investment allowance, if any, still outstanding to the amalgamating`
  line `company in respect of such ship, aircraft, machinery or plant, shall be allowed to the`
  line `amalgamated company in accordance with the provisions of sub-section ( 3 ), so, however, that`
  line `the total period for which the balance of investment allowance shall be carried forward in the`
  line `assessments of the amalgamating company and the amalgamated company shall not exceed`
  line `the period of eight years specified in sub-section ( 3 ) and the amalgamated company shall be`
  line `treated as the assessee in respect of such ship, aircraft, machinery or plant for the purposes of`
  line `this section.`
  line `( 7 ) Where a firm is succeeded to by a company in the business carried on by it as a result of`
  line `which the firm sells or otherwise transfers to the company any ship, aircraft, machinery or plant,`
  line `the provisions of clauses ( a ) and ( b ) of sub-section ( 6 ) shall, so far as may be, apply to the firm`
  line `and the company.`
  line `Explanation. — The provisions of this sub-section shall apply only where —`
  line `( i ) all the property of the firm relating to the business immediately before the succession`
  line `becomes the property of the company;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 6, for “the proviso” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
