  content obj_root_law_sections_162_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes
  sourcePage 162
obj_root_law_sections_162_content:
  string
  line 162
  line `( ii ) all the liabilities of the firm relating to the business immediately before the succession`
  line `become the liabilities of the company; and`
  line `( iii ) all the shareholders of the company were partners of the firm immediately before the`
  line succession.
  line `( 8 ) The Central Government, if it considers necessary or expedient so to do, may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, direct that the deduction allowable under this section shall not`
  line `be allowed in respect of any ship or aircraft acquired or any machinery or plant installed after`
  line `such date 1 *** as may be specified therein.`
  line `2 [( 8A ) The Central Government, if it considers necessary or expedient so to do, may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, omit any article or thing from the list of articles or things`
  line `specified in the Eleventh Schedule.]`
  line `3 [( 8B ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 8 ) or the notification of the`
  line `Government of India in the Ministry of Finance (Department of Revenue) No. GSR 870(E), dated`
  line `the 12th June, 1986, issued thereunder, the provisions of this section shall apply in respect of, —`
  line `( a ) ( i ) a new ship or new aircraft acquired after the 31st day of March, 1987 but before`
  line `the 1st day of April, 1988, if the assessee furnishes evidence to the satisfaction of the`
  line `Assessing Officer that he had, before the 12th day of June, 1986, entered into a contract for`
  line `the purchase of such ship or aircraft with the builder or manu-facturer or owner thereof, as the`
  line `case may be;`
  line `( ii ) any new machinery or plant installed after the 31st day of March, 1987 but before the`
  line `1st day of April, 1988, if the assessee furnishes evidence to the satisfaction of the Assessing`
  line `Officer that before the 12th day of June, 1986, he had purchased such machinery or plant or`
  line `had entered into a contract for the purchase of such machinery or plant with the manufacturer`
  line `or owner of, or a dealer in, such machinery or plant, or had, where such machinery or plant`
  line `has been manufactured in an undertaking owned by the assessee, taken steps for the`
  line `manufacture of such machinery or plant:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in sub-section ( 1 ) shall entitle the assessee to claim`
  line `deduction in respect of a ship or aircraft or machinery or plant referred to in this clause in any`
  line `previous year except the previous year relevant to the assessment year commencing on the 1st`
  line `day of April, 1989;`
  line `( b ) a new ship or new aircraft acquired or any new machinery or plant installed after the`
  line `31st day of March, 1988, but before such date as the Central Government, if it considers`
  line `necessary or expedient so to do, may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this`
  line behalf.
  line `( 8C ) Subject to the provisions of clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 3 ), where a deduction has been`
  line `allowed to an assessee under sub-section ( 1 ) in any assessment year, no deduction shall be`
  line `allowed to the assessee under section 32AB in the said assessment year (hereinafter referred to as`
  line `the initial assessment year) and a block of further period of four years beginning with the`
  line `assessment year immediately succeeding the initial assessment year.]`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `1. The words “, not being earlier than three years from the date of such notification,” omitted by Act 23 of 1986, s. 7`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1986).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-1978).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 6, for sub-section ( 8B ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. Sub-section ( 9 ) omitted by Act 12 of 1990, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
