obj_root_law_sections_163_content:
  string
  line 163
  line `1 [ 32AB. Investment deposit account. — ( 1 ) Subject to the other provisions of this section, where an`
  line `assessee, whose total income includes income chargeable to tax under the head “Profits and gains of`
  line `business or profession”, has, out of such income,—`
  line `( a ) deposited any amount in an account (hereafter in this section referred to as deposit account)`
  line `maintained by him with the Development Bank before the expiry of six months from the end of the`
  line `previous year or before furnishing the return of his income, whichever is earlier; or`
  line `( b ) utilised any amount during the previous year for the purchase of any new ship, new aircraft,`
  line `new machinery or plant, without depositing any amount in the deposit account under clause ( a ),`
  line `in accordance with, and for the purposes specified in, a scheme (hereafter in this section referred to as the`
  line `scheme) to be framed by the Central Government, or if the assessee is carrying on the business of`
  line `growing and manufacturing tea in India, to be approved in this behalf by the Tea Board, the assessee shall`
  line `be allowed a 2 [deduction (such deduction being allowed before the loss, if any, brought forward from`
  line `earlier years is set off under section 72) of] —`
  line `( i ) a sum equal to the amount, or the aggregate of the amounts, so deposited and any amount so`
  line `utilised; or`
  line `( ii ) a sum equal to twenty per cent. of the profits of 3 *** business or profession as computed in`
  line `the accounts of the assessee audited in accordance with sub-section ( 5 ),`
  line `whichever is less:`
  line `4 [Provided that where such assessee is a firm, or any association of persons or any body of`
  line `individuals, the deduction under this section shall not be allowed in the computation of the income of any`
  line `partner, or as the case may be, any member of such firm, association of persons or body of individuals:]`
  line `5 [Provided further that no such deduction shall be allowed in relation to the assessment year`
  line `commencing on the 1st day of April, 1991, or any subsequent assessment year.]`
  line `( 2 ) For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `6 * * * * *`
  line `7 [( ii ) “new ship” or “new aircraft” includes a ship or aircraft which before the date of acquisition`
  line `by the assessee was used by any other person, if it was not at any time previous to the date of such`
  line `acquisition owned by any person resident in India;`
  line `( iii ) “new machinery or plant” includes machinery or plant which before its installation by the`
  line `assessee was used outside India by any other person, if the following conditions are fulfilled,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( a ) such machinery or plant was not, at any time previous to the date of such installation by`
  line `the assessee, used in India;`
  line `( b ) such machinery or plant is imported into India from any country outside India; and`
  line `( c ) no deduction on account of depreciation in respect of such machinery or plant has been`
  line `allowed or is allowable under this Act in computing the total income of any person for any period`
  line `prior to the date of the installation of the machinery or plant by the assessee;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 1986, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 7, for “deduction of” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1987).`
  line `3. The word “eligible” omitted by Act 13 of 1989, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1991).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `6. Clause ( i ) omitted by Act 13 of 1989, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 7 for clause ( ii ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
