obj_root_law_sections_164_content:
  string
  line 164
  line `( iv ) “Tea Board” means the Tea Board established under section 4 of the Tea`
  line `Act, 1953 (29 of 1953).]`
  line `( 3 ) 1 [The profits of business or profession of an assessee for the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ) shall] be`
  line `an amount arrived at after deducting an amount equal to the depreciation computed in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 32 from the amounts of profits computed in accordance with`
  line `the requirements of Parts II and III of the 2 [Schedule VI] to the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956),`
  line `3 [as increased by the aggregate of —`
  line `( i ) the amount of depreciation;`
  line `( ii ) the amount of income-tax paid or payable, and provision therefor;`
  line `( iii ) the amount of surtax paid or payable under the Companies (Profits) Surtax Act, 1964 (7 of`
  line `1964);`
  line `( iv ) the amounts carried to any reserves, by whatever name called;`
  line `( v ) the amount or amounts set aside to provisions made for meeting liabilities, other than`
  line `ascertained liabilities;`
  line `( vi ) the amount by way of provision for losses of subsidiary companies; and`
  line `( vii ) the amount or amounts of dividends paid or proposed,`
  line `if any debited to the profit and loss account; and as reduced by any amount or amounts withdrawn from`
  line `reserves or provisions, if such amounts are credited to the profit and loss account 4 ***.]`
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `( 4 ) No deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be allowed in respect of any amount utilised for the`
  line `purchase of —`
  line `( a ) any machinery or plant to be installed in any office premises or residential accommodation,`
  line `including any accommodation in the nature of a guest-house;`
  line `( b ) any office appliances (not being computers);`
  line `( c ) any road transport vehicles;`
  line `( d ) any machinery or plant, the whole of the actual cost of which is allowed as a deduction`
  line `(whether by way of depreciation or otherwise) in computing the income chargeable under the head`
  line `“Profits and gains of business or profession” of any one previous year;`
  line `6 [( e ) any new machinery or plant to be installed in an industrial undertaking, other than a small-`
  line `scale industrial undertaking, as defined in section 80HHA, for the purposes of business of`
  line `construction, manufacture or production of any article or thing specified in the list in the Eleventh`
  line Schedule.]
  line `( 5 ) The deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall not be admissible unless the accounts of the business or`
  line `profession of the assessee for the previous year relevant to the assessment year for which the deduction is`
  line `claimed have been audited by an accountant as defined in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 288 and the assessee furnishes, along with his return of income, the report of such audit in the`
  line `prescribed form duly signed and verified by such accountant:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 1989, s. 7, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for “Sixth Schedule” ( w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 7, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `4. The word “and” omitted by Act 13 of 1989, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1991).`
  line `5. Clause ( b ) omitted by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `6. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_165:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-165
  sectionNo (165)
  orderNo 165
  title `Page 165`
  content obj_root_law_sections_165_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes
  sourcePage 165
obj_root_law_sections_165_content:
  string
  line 165
  line `Provided that in a case where the assessee is required by or under any other law to get his accounts`
  line `audited, it shall be sufficient compliance with the provisions of this sub-section if such assessee gets the`
  line `accounts of such business or profession audited under such law and furnishes the report of the audit as`
  line `required under such other law and a further report in the form prescribed under this sub-section.`
  line `1 [( 5A ) Any amount standing to the credit of the assessee in the deposit account shall not be allowed to`
  line `be withdrawn before the expiry of a period of five years from the date of deposit except for the purposes`
  line `specified in the 2 [scheme or] in the circumstances specified below: —`
  line `( a ) closure of business;`
  line `( b ) death of an assessee;`
  line `( c ) partition of a Hindu undivided family;`
  line `( d ) dissolution of a firm;`
  line `( e ) liquidation of a company.`
  line `3 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that nothing contained in this sub-`
  line `section shall affect the operation of the provisions of sub-section ( 5AA ) or sub-section ( 6 ) in relation to`
  line `any withdrawals made from the deposit account either before or after the expiry of a period of five years`
  line `from the date of deposit.]`
  line `3 [( 5AA ) Where any amount, standing to the credit of the assessee in the deposit account, is withdrawn`
  line `during any previous year by the assessee in the circumstance specified in clause ( a ) or clause ( d ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 5A ), the whole of such amount shall be deemed to be the profits and gains of business or`
  line `profession of that previous year and shall accordingly be chargeable to income-tax as the income of that`
  line `previous year, as if the business had not closed or, as the case may be, the firm had not been dissolved.]`
  line `( 5B ) Where any amount standing to the credit of the assessee in the deposit account is utilised by the`
  line `assessee for the purposes of any expenditure in connection with the 4 *** business or profession in`
  line `accordance with the scheme, such expenditure shall not be allowed in computing the income chargeable`
  line `under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession”. ]`
  line `( 6 ) Where any amount, standing to the credit of the assessee in the deposit account, released during`
  line `any previous year by the Development Bank for being utilised by the assessee for the purposes specified`
  line `in the scheme or at the closure of the account 5 [in circumstances other than the circumstances specified in`
  line `clauses ( b ), ( c ) and ( e ) of sub-section ( 5A )], 6 [is not utilised in accordance with and within the time`
  line `specified in, the scheme], either wholly or in part, 7 *** the whole of such amount or, as the case may be,`
  line `part thereof which is not so utilised shall be deemed to be the profits and gains of business or profession`
  line `of that previous year and shall accordingly be chargeable to income-tax as the income of that previous`
  line year.
  line `( 7 ) Where any asset acquired in accordance with the scheme is sold or otherwise transferred in any`
  line `previous year by the assessee to any person at any time before the expiry of eight years from the end of`
  line `the previous year in which it was acquired, such part of the cost of such asset as is relatable to the`
  line `deductions allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to be the profits and gains of business or`
  line `profession of the previous year in which the asset is sold or otherwise transferred and shall accordingly be`
  line `chargeable to income-tax as the income of that previous year:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 1989, s. 7, for “scheme and” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1987).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `4. The word “eligible” omitted by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 7 for “is not utilised in accordance with the scheme” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1987).`
  line `7. The words “within the previous year” omitted by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f 1-4-1987).`
