obj_root_law_sections_166_content:
  string
  line 166
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply —`
  line `( i ) where the asset is sold or otherwise transferred by the assessee to Government, a local`
  line `authority, a corporation established by or under a Central, State or Provincial Act or a Government`
  line `company as defined in section 617 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956); or`
  line `( ii ) where the sale or transfer of the asset is made in connection with the succession of a firm by a`
  line `company in the business or profession carried on by the firm as a result of which the firm sells or`
  line `otherwise transfers to the company any asset and the scheme continues to apply to the company in the`
  line `manner applicable to the firm.`
  line `Explanation. — The provisions of clause ( ii ) of the proviso shall apply only where —`
  line `( i ) all the properties of the firm relating to the business or profession immediately before the`
  line `succession become the properties of the company;`
  line `( ii ) all the liabilities of the firm relating to the business or profession immediately before the`
  line `succession become the liabilities of the company; and`
  line `( iii ) all the shareholders of the company were partners of the firm immediately before the`
  line succession.
  line `( 8 ) The Central Government may, if it considers it necessary or expedient so to do, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, omit any article or thing from the list of articles or things specified in the Eleventh`
  line Schedule.
  line `( 9 ) The Central Government may, after making such inquiry as it may think fit, direct, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, that the provisions of this section shall not apply to any class of assessees, with`
  line `effect from such date as it may specify in the notification.`
  line `1 [( 10 ) Where a deduction has been allowed to an assessee under this section in any assessment year,`
  line `no deduction shall be allowed to the assessee under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 32A in the said assessment`
  line `year (hereinafter referred to as the initial assessment year) and a block of further period of four years`
  line `beginning with the assessment year immediately succeeding the initial assessment year.]`
  line `Explanation. — In this section, —`
  line `( a ) “computers” does not include calculating machines and calculating devices;`
  line `( b ) “Development Bank” means—`
  line `( i ) in the case of an assessee carrying on business of growing and manufacturing tea in`
  line `India, the National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development established under section 3 of`
  line `the National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development Act, 1981 (61 of 1981);`
  line `( ii ) in the case of other assessees, the Industrial Development Bank of India established`
  line `under the Industrial Development Bank of India Act, 1964 (18 of 1964) and includes such bank`
  line `or institution as may be specified in the scheme in this behalf.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 7, for sub-section ( 10 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
