obj_root_law_sections_168_content:
  string
  line 168
  line `( iii ) any office appliances including computers or computer software;`
  line `( iv ) any vehicle; or`
  line `( v ) any plant or machinery, the whole of the actual cost of which is allowed as deduction`
  line `(whether by way of depreciation or otherwise) in computing the income chargeable under the head`
  line `“Profits and gains of business or profession” of any previous year.]`
  line `1 [ 32AD. Investment in new plant or machinery in notified backward areas in certain`
  line `States. — ( 1 ) Where an assessee, sets up an undertaking or enterprise for manufacture or production of`
  line `any article or thing, on or after the 1st day of April, 2015 in any backward area notified by the Central`
  line `Government in this behalf, in the State of Andhra Pradesh or in the State of Bihar or in the State of`
  line `Telangana or in the State of West Bengal, and acquires and installs any new asset for the purposes of the`
  line `said undertaking or enterprise during the period beginning on the 1st day of April, 2015 and ending`
  line `before the 1st day of April, 2020 in the said backward area, then, there shall be allowed a deduction of a`
  line `sum equal to fifteen per cent. of the actual cost of such new asset for the assessment year relevant to the`
  line `previous year in which such new asset is installed.`
  line `( 2 ) If any new asset acquired and installed by the assessee is sold or otherwise transferred, except in`
  line `connection with the amalgamation or demerger or re-organisation of business referred to in clause ( xiii ) or`
  line `clause ( xiiib ) or clause ( xiv ) of section 47, within a period of five years from the date of its installation,`
  line `the amount of deduction allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) in respect of such new asset shall be deemed to be`
  line `the income of the assessee chargeable under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession” of the`
  line `previous year in which such new asset is sold or otherwise transferred, in addition to taxability of gains,`
  line `arising on account of transfer of such new asset.`
  line `( 3 ) Where the new asset is sold or otherwise transferred in connection with the amalgamation or`
  line `demerger or re-organisation of business referred to in clause ( xiii ) or clause ( xiiib ) or clause ( xiv ) of`
  line `section 47 within a period of five years from the date of its installation, the provisions of sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `shall apply to the amalgamated company or the resulting company or the successor referred to in`
  line `clause ( xiii ) or clause ( xiiib ) or clause ( xiv ) of section 47, as the case may be, as they would have applied`
  line `to the amalgamating company or the demerged company or the predecessor referred to in clause ( xiii ) or`
  line `clause ( xiiib ) or clause ( xiv ) of section 47.`
  line `( 4 ) For the purposes of this section, “new asset” means any new plant or machinery (other than a ship`
  line `or aircraft) but does not include —`
  line `( a ) any plant or machinery, which before its installation by the assessee, was used either within or`
  line `outside India by any other person;`
  line `( b ) any plant or machinery installed in any office premises or any residential accommodation,`
  line `including accommodation in the nature of a guest house;`
  line `( c ) any office appliances including computers or computer software;`
  line `( d ) any vehicle; or`
  line `( e ) any plant or machinery, the whole of the actual cost of which is allowed as deduction`
  line `(whether by way of depreciation or otherwise) in computing the income chargeable under the head`
  line `“Profits and gains of business or profession” of any previous year. ]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
