obj_root_law_sections_170_content:
  string
  line 170
  line `be allowed as a deduction a sum by way of development rebate at such rate or rates as may be prescribed,`
  line `provided that the following conditions are fulfilled, namely: —`
  line `( i ) such ship was not previous to the date of such acquisition owned at any time by any person`
  line `resident in India;`
  line `( ii ) such ship is wholly used for the purposes of the business carried on by the assessee; and`
  line `( iii ) such other conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line `( b ) An assessee who installs any machinery or plant (other than office appliances or road transport`
  line `vehicles) which before such installation by the assessee was used outside India by any other person shall,`
  line `subject to the provisions of section 34, also be allowed as a deduction a sum by way of development`
  line `rebate at such rate or rates as may be prescribed, provided that the following conditions are fulfilled,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( i ) such machinery or plant was not used in India at any time previous to the date of such`
  line `installation by the assessee;`
  line `( ii ) it is imported in India by the assessee from any country outside India;`
  line `( iii ) no deduction on account of depreciation or development rebate in respect of such machinery`
  line `or plant has been allowed or is allowable under the provisions of the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11`
  line `of 1922), or this Act in computing the total income of any person for any period prior to the date of`
  line `the installation of the machinery or plant by the assessee;`
  line `( iv ) such machinery or plant is wholly used for the purposes of the business carried on by the`
  line `assessee; and`
  line `( v ) such other conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line `( c ) The development rebate under this sub-section shall be allowed as a deduction in respect of the`
  line `previous year in which the ship was acquired or the machinery or plant was installed or, if the ship,`
  line `machinery or plant is first put to use in the immediately succeeding previous year, then, in respect of that`
  line `previous year.]`
  line `( 2 ) In the case of a ship acquired or machinery or plant installed after the 31st day of`
  line `December, 1957, where the total income of the assessee assessable for the assessment year relevant to the`
  line `previous year in which the ship was acquired or the machinery or plant installed or the immediately`
  line `succeeding previous year, as the case may be 1 [(the total income for this purpose being computed without`
  line `making any allowance under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 1A ) of this section or sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 33A or any deduction under Chapter VIA 2 ***] is nil or is less than the full amount of the`
  line `development rebate calculated 3 [at the rate applicable thereto 4 [under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 1A ),`
  line `as the case may be], —`
  line `( i ) the sum to be allowed by way of development rebate for that assessment year 4 [under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 1A )] shall be only such amount as is sufficient to reduce the said total`
  line `income to nil; and`
  line `( ii ) the amount of the development rebate, to the extent to which it has not been allowed as`
  line `aforesaid, shall be carried forward to the following assessment year, and the development rebate to be`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 33 and the third Schedule, for certain brackets, words, figures and letters (w.e.f. 1-4-1968).`
  line `2. The words, figures and letter “or section 280 - O” omitted by Act 26 of 1988, s. 54 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 5 of 1964, s. 8, for “at the rate applicable thereto under that sub - section” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for “under sub -section ( 1 )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
