  title `Page 171`
  content obj_root_law_sections_171_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes
  sourcePage 171
obj_root_law_sections_171_content:
  string
  line 171
  line `allowed for the following assessment year shall be such amount as is sufficient to reduce the total`
  line `income of the assessee assessable for that assessment year, computed in the manner aforesaid, to nil,`
  line `and the balance of the development rebate, if any, still outstanding shall be carried forward to the`
  line `following assessment year and so on, so however, that no portion of the development rebate shall be`
  line `carried forward for more than eight assessment years immediately succeeding the assessment year`
  line `relevant to the previous year in which the ship was acquired or the machinery or plant installed or the`
  line `immediately succeeding previous year, as the case may be.`
  line `Explanation. — Where for any assessment year development rebate is to be allowed in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) in respect of ships acquired or machinery or plant installed in`
  line `more than one previous year, and the total income of the assessee assessable for that assessment year`
  line `1 [(the total income for this purpose being computed without making any allowance under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 1A ) of this section or sub-section ( 1 ) of section 33A or any deduction`
  line `under Chapter VI-A 2 ***] is less than the aggregate of the amounts due to be allowed in respect of the`
  line `assets aforesaid for that assessment year, the following procedure shall be followed, namely: —`
  line `( i ) the allowance under clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 2 ) shall be made before any allowance`
  line `under clause ( i ) of that sub-section is made; and`
  line `( ii ) where an allowance has to be made under clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 2 ) in respect of`
  line `amounts carried forward from more than one assessment year, the amount carried forward from`
  line `an earlier assessment year shall be allowed before any amount carried forward from a later`
  line `assessment year.`
  line `3 [( 3 ) Where, in a scheme of amalgamation, the amalgamating company sells or otherwise transfers to`
  line `the amalgamated company any ship, machinery or plant in respect of which development rebate has been`
  line `allowed to the amalgamating company under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 1A ), —`
  line `( a ) the amalgamated company shall continue to fulfil the conditions mentioned in sub-section ( 3 )`
  line `of section 34 in respect of the reserve created by the amalgamating company and in respect of the`
  line `period within which such ship, machinery or plant shall not be sold or otherwise transferred and in`
  line `default of any of these conditions, the provisions of sub-section ( 5 ) of section 155 shall apply to the`
  line `amalgamated company as they would have applied to the amalgamating company had it committed`
  line `the default; and`
  line `( b ) the balance of development rebate, if any, still outstanding to the amalgamating company in`
  line `respect of such ship, machinery or plant shall be allowed to the amalgamated company in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ), so, however, that the total period for which the balance of`
  line `development rebate shall be carried forward in the assessments of the amalgamating company and the`
  line `amalgamated company shall not exceed the period of eight years specified in sub-section ( 2 ) and the`
  line `amalgamated company shall be treated as the assessee in respect of such ship, machinery or plant for`
  line `the purposes of this section and section 34.]`
  line `( 4 ) Where a firm is succeeded to by a company in the business carried on by it as a result of which`
  line `the firm sells or otherwise transfers to the company any ship, machinery or plant, the provisions of`
  line `clauses ( a ) and ( b ) of sub-section ( 3 ) shall, so far as may be, apply to the firm and the company.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 33 and the Third Schedule, for certain brackets, words, figures and letters (w.e.f. 1-4-1968).`
  line `2. The words, figures and letter “or section 280 - O” omitted by Act 26 of 1988, s. 54 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 9, for sub-section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1967).`
