obj_root_law_sections_172_content:
  string
  line 172
  line `Explanation. — The provisions of this clause shall apply only where —`
  line `( i ) all the property of the firm relating to the business immediately before the succession`
  line `becomes the property of the company;`
  line `( ii ) all the liabilities of the firm relating to the business immediately before the succession`
  line `become the liabilities of the company; and`
  line `( iii ) all the shareholders of the company were partners of the firm immediately before the`
  line succession.
  line `1 [( 5 ) The Central Government, if it considers it necessary or expedient so to do, may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, direct that the deduction allowable under this section shall not be allowed in`
  line `respect of a ship acquired or machinery or plant installed after such date, not being earlier than three years`
  line `from the date of such notification, as may be specified therein.]`
  line `2 [( 6 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, no deduction by`
  line `way of development rebate shall be allowed in respect of any machinery or plant installed after the 31st`
  line `day of March, 1965, in any office premises or any residential accommodation, including any`
  line `accommodation in the nature of a guest-house:]`
  line `3 [Provided that the provisions of this sub-section shall not apply in the case of an assessee being an`
  line `Indian company, in respect of any machinery or plant installed by it in premises used by it as a hotel,`
  line `where the hotel is for the time being approved in this behalf by the Central Government.]`
  line `4 [ 33A. Development allowance. — ( 1 ) In respect of planting of tea bushes on any land in India owned`
  line `by an assessee who carries on business of growing and manufacturing tea in India, a sum by way of`
  line `development allowance equivalent to —`
  line `( i ) where tea bushes have been planted on any land not planted at any time with tea bushes or on`
  line `any land which had been previously abandoned, 5 [fifty per cent..] of the actual cost of planting; and`
  line `( ii ) where tea bushes are planted in replacement of tea bushes that have died or have become`
  line `permanently useless on any land already planted, 6 [thirty per cent..] of the actual cost of planting,`
  line `shall, subject to the provisions of this section, 7 [be allowed as a deduction in the manner specified`
  line `hereunder, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the amount of the development allowance shall, in the first instance, be computed with`
  line `reference to that portion of the actual cost of planting which is incurred during the previous year in`
  line `which the land is prepared for planting or replanting, as the case may be, and in the previous year`
  line `next following, and the amount so computed shall be allowed as a deduction in respect of such`
  line `previous year next following; and`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 5 of 1964, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-1964).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 33 and the Third Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-1968).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 13 of 1966, s. 8, for “forty per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1966).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for “twenty per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1966).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for “be allowed as a deduction in respect of the third secceeding previous year next following he`
  line `previous year in which the land is prepared for planting or replanting, as the case may be” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1966).`
obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_173:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-173
  sectionNo (173)
  orderNo 173
  title `Page 173`
  content obj_root_law_sections_173_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes
  sourcePage 173
obj_root_law_sections_173_content:
  string
  line 173
  line `( b ) thereafter, the development allowance shall again be computed with reference to the actual`
  line `cost of planting, and if the sum so computed exceeds the amount allowed as a deduction under clause`
  line `( a ), the amount of the excess shall be allowed as a deduction in respect of the third succeeding`
  line `previous year next following the previous year in which the land has been prepared for planting or`
  line `replanting, as the case may be:]`
  line `1 [Provided that no deduction under clause ( i ) shall be allowed unless the planting has commenced`
  line `after the 31st day of March, 1965, and been completed before the 1st day of April, 1990:`
  line `Provided further that no deduction shall be allowed under clause ( ii ) unless the planting has`
  line `commenced after the 31st day of March, 1965, and been completed before the 1st day of April, 1970.]`
  line `( 2 ) Where the total income of the assessee assessable for the assessment year relevant to`
  line `2 [the previous year in respect of which the deduction is required to be allowed under sub-section ( 1 )]`
  line `3 [(the total income for this purpose being computed after deduction of the allowance under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `or sub-section ( 1A ) or clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 33, but without making any deduction under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of this section or any deduction under Chapter VI-A 4 ***)] is nil or is less than the full`
  line `amount of the development allowance 5 [calculated at the rates and in the manner specified in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 )] —`
  line `( i ) the sum to be allowed by way of development allowance for that assessment year under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) shall be only such amount as is sufficient to reduce the said total income to nil; and`
  line `( ii ) the amount of the development allowance, to the extent to which it has not been allowed as`
  line `aforesaid, shall be carried forward to the following assessment year, and the development allowance`
  line `to be allowed for the following assessment year shall be such amount as is sufficient to reduce the`
  line `total income of the assessee assessable for that assessment year, computed in the manner aforesaid,`
  line `to nil, and the balance of the development allowance, if any, still outstanding shall be carried forward`
  line `to the following assessment year and so on, so, however, that no portion of the development`
  line `allowance shall be carried forward for more than eight assessment years immediately succeeding the`
  line `assessment year in which the deduction was first allowable.`
  line `Explanation. — Where for any assessment year development allowance is to be allowed in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) in respect of more than one previous year, and the`
  line `total income of the assessee assessable for that assessment year 3 [(the total income for this purpose`
  line `being computed after deduction of the allowance under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 1A ) or`
  line `clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 33, but without making any deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `this section or any deduction under Chapter VIA 4 *** )] is less than the amount of the development`
  line `allowance due to be made in respect of that assessment year, the following procedure shall be`
  line `followed, namely: —`
  line `( i ) the allowance under clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of this section shall be made before any`
  line `allowance under clause ( i ) of that sub-section is made; and`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 9, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 1966, s. 8, for “the third succeeding previous year next following the previous year in which the land`
  line `has been prepared” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1966).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 33 and the third Schedule, for “(the total income for this purpose being c omputed after`
  line `making the allowance under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 1A ) or clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 33 but without`
  line `making any allowance under sub-section ( 1 ) of this section” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1968).`
  line `4. The words, figures and letter “or sec tion 280- O” omitted by Act 26 of 1988, s. 54 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 13 of 1966, s. 8, for “calculated at the rates specified in sub -section ( 1 )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1966).`
obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes:
