  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes
  sourcePage 174
obj_root_law_sections_174_content:
  string
  line 174
  line `( ii ) where an allowance has to be made under clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of this section in`
  line `respect of amounts carried forward from more than one assessment year, the amount carried`
  line `forward from an earlier assessment year shall be allowed before any amount carried forward from`
  line `a later assessment year.`
  line `( 3 ) The deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be allowed only if the following conditions are`
  line `fulfilled, namely: —`
  line `( i ) the particulars prescribed in this behalf have been furnished by the assessee;`
  line `( ii ) an amount equal to seventy-five per cent. of the development allowance to be actually`
  line `allowed is debited to the profit and loss account of the relevant previous year and credited to a reserve`
  line `account to be utilised by the assessee during a period of eight years next following for the purposes of`
  line `the business of the undertaking, other than —`
  line `( a ) for distribution by way of dividends or profits; or`
  line `( b ) for remittance outside India as profits or for the creation of any asset outside India; and`
  line `( iii ) such other conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 4 ) If any such land is sold or otherwise transferred by the assessee to any person at any time before`
  line `the expiry of eight years from the end of the previous year in which the deduction under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `was allowed, any allowance under this section shall be deemed to have been wrongly made for the`
  line `purposes of this Act, and the provisions of sub-section ( 5A ) of section 155 shall apply accordingly:`
  line `Provided that this sub-section shall not apply —`
  line `( i ) where the land is sold or otherwise transferred by the assessee to the Government, a local`
  line `authority, a corporation established by a Central, State or Provincial Act, or a Government`
  line `company as defined in section 617 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956); or`
  line `( ii ) where the sale or transfer of the land is made in connection with the amalgamation or`
  line `succession referred to in sub-section ( 5 ) or sub-section ( 6 ).`
  line `1 [( 5 ) Where, in a scheme of amalgamation, the amalgamating company sells or otherwise transfers to`
  line `the amalgamated company any land in respect of which development allowance has been allowed to the`
  line `amalgamating company under sub-section ( 1 ), —`
  line `( a ) the amalgamated company shall continue to fulfil the conditions mentioned in sub-section ( 3 )`
  line `in respect of the reserve created by the amalgamating company and in respect of the period within`
  line `which such land shall not be sold or otherwise transferred and in default of any of these conditions,`
  line `the provisions of sub-section ( 5A ) of section 155 shall apply to the amalgamated company as they`
  line `would have applied to the amalgamating company had it committed the default; and`
  line `( b ) the balance of development allowance, if any, still outstanding to the amalgamating company`
  line `in respect of such land shall be allowed to the amalgamated company in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of sub-section ( 2 ), so, however, that the total period for which the balance of development`
  line `allowance shall be carried forward in the assessments of the amalgamating company and the`
  line `amalgamated company shall not exceed the period of eight years specified in sub-section ( 2 ) and the`
  line `amalgamated company shall be treated as the assessee in respect of such land for the purposes of this`
  line section.
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 10, for sub-section ( 5 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1967).`
obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes:
