  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes
  sourcePage 176
obj_root_law_sections_176_content:
  string
  line 176
  line `1 [ 33AB. Tea development account 2 [, coffee development account and rubber development`
  line `account]. — ( 1 ) Where an assessee carrying on business of 3 [growing and manufacturing tea or coffee or`
  line `rubber] in India has, before the expiry of six months from the end of the previous year or before 4 [the due`
  line `date of furnishing the return of his income], 5 [whichever is earlier, —`
  line `( a ) deposited with the National Bank any amount or amounts in an account (hereafter in this`
  line `section referred to as the special account) maintained by the assessee with that Bank in accordance`
  line `with, and for the purposes specified in, a scheme (hereafter in this section referred to as the scheme)`
  line `6 [approved in this behalf by the Tea Board or the Coffee Board or the Rubber Board]; or`
  line `( b ) 7 [deposited any amount in an account (hereafter in this section referred to as the Deposit`
  line `Account) opened by the assessee in accordance with, and for the purposes specified in, a scheme`
  line `framed by the Tea Board or the Coffee Board or the Rubber Board, as the case may be (hereafter in`
  line `this section referred to as the deposit scheme), with the previous approval of the Central`
  line Government,]
  line `the assessee shall, subject to the provisions of this section,] be allowed a deduction (such deduction being`
  line `allowed before the loss, if any, brought forward from earlier years is set off under section 72 ) of —`
  line `( a ) a sum equal to the amount or the aggregate of the amounts so deposited; or`
  line `( b ) 8 [a sum equal to forty per cent.. of the profits] of such business (computed under the head`
  line `“Profits and gains of business or profession” before making any deduction under this section),`
  line `whichever is less:`
  line `Provided that where such assessee is a firm, or any association of persons or any body of individuals,`
  line `the deduction under this section shall not be allowed in the computation of the income of any partner, or`
  line `as the case may be, any member of such firm, association of persons or body of individuals:`
  line `Provided further that where any deduction, in respect of any amount deposited in the special account`
  line `9 [, or in the 10 [Deposit Account], has been allowed under this sub-section in any previous year, no`
  line `deduction shall be allowed in respect of such amount in any other previous year.`
  line `( 2 ) The deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall not be admissible unless the accounts of such business`
  line `of the assessee for the previous year relevant to the assessment year for which the deduction is claimed`
  line `have been audited by an accountant as defined in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288`
  line `and the assessee furnishes, along with his return of income, the report of such audit in the prescribed`
  line `formduly signed and verified by such accountant:`
  line `Provided that in a case where the assessee is required by or under any other law to get his accounts`
  line `audited, it shall be sufficient compliance with the provisions of this sub-section if such assessee gets the`
  line `accounts of such business audited under such law and furnishes the report of the audit as required under`
  line `such other law and a further report in the form prescribed under this sub-section.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 10, for section 33AB (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for “growing and manufacturing tea” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2004).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for “furnishing the return of his income” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2004).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 12, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 16, for “approved in this behalf by the Tea Board” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2004).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `8. Subs.by Act 14 of 2001, s. 22, for “a sum equal to twenty per cent. of the profits” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2002).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 16, for “Tea Deposit Account” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_177:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-177
  sectionNo (177)
