  title `Page 177`
  content obj_root_law_sections_177_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes
  sourcePage 177
obj_root_law_sections_177_content:
  string
  line 177
  line `( 3 ) Any amount standing to the credit of the assessee in 1 [the special account or the 2 [Deposit`
  line `Account] shall not be allowed to be withdrawn except for the purposes specified in the scheme or, as the`
  line `case may be, in the deposit scheme] or in the circumstances specified below: —`
  line `( a ) closure of business;`
  line `( b ) death of an assessee;`
  line `( c ) partition of a Hindu undivided family;`
  line `( d ) dissolution of a firm;`
  line `( e ) liquidation of a company.`
  line `3 [( 4 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 3 ), where any amount standing to the credit`
  line `of the assessee in the special account or in the Deposit Account is released during any previous year by`
  line `the National Bank or withdrawn by the assessee from the Deposit Account, and such amount is utilised`
  line `for the purchase of —`
  line `( a ) any machinery or plant to be installed in any office premises or residential accommodation,`
  line `including any accommodation in the nature of a guest-house;`
  line `( b ) any office appliances (not being computers);`
  line `( c ) any machinery or plant, the whole of the actual cost of which is allowed as a deduction`
  line `(whether by way of depreciation or otherwise) in computing the income chargeable under the head`
  line `“Profits and gains of business or profession” of any one previous year;`
  line `( d ) any new machinery or plant to be installed in an industrial undertaking for the purposes of`
  line `business of construction, manufacture or production of any article or thing specified in the list in the`
  line `Eleventh Schedule,`
  line `the whole of such amount so utilised shall be deemed to be the profits and gains of business of that`
  line `previous year and shall accordingly be chargeable to income-tax as the income of that previous year.]`
  line `( 5 ) Where any amount, standing to the credit of the assessee in the special account 4 [or in the`
  line `2 [Deposit Account]], is withdrawn during any previous year by the assessee in the circumstance specified`
  line `in clause ( a ) or clause ( d ) of sub-section ( 3 ), the whole of such amount shall be deemed to be the profits`
  line `and gains of business or profession of that previous year and shall accordingly be chargeable to income-`
  line `tax as the income of that previous year, as if the business had not closed or, as the case may be, the firm`
  line `had not been dissolved.`
  line `( 6 ) Where any amount standing to the credit of the assessee in the special account 4 [or in the`
  line `2 [Deposit Account]] is utilised by the assessee for the purposes of any expenditure in connection with`
  line `such business in accordance with the scheme 4 [or the deposit scheme], such expenditure shall not be`
  line `allowed in computing the income chargeable under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession.`
  line `( 7 ) Where any amount, standing to the credit of the assessee in the special account 4 [or in the`
  line `2 [Deposit Account]], which is released during any previous year by the National Bank 4 [or which is`
  line `withdrawn by the assessee from the 2 [Deposit Account]]for being utilised by the assessee for the purposes`
  line `of such business in accordance with the scheme 4 [or the deposit scheme] is not so utilised, either wholly`
  line `or in part, within that previous year, the whole of such amount or, as the case may be, part thereof which`
  line `is not so utilised shall be deemed to be profits and gains of business and accordingly chargeable to`
  line `income-tax as the income of that previous year:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 12, for “the special account shall not be allowed to be withdrawn except for the purposes`
  line `spe cified in the scheme” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1995).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 16, for “Tea Deposit Account” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2004).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for sub-section ( 4 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_178:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-178
  sectionNo (178)
  orderNo 178
  title `Page 178`
  content obj_root_law_sections_178_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes
  sourcePage 178
obj_root_law_sections_178_content:
  string
  line 178
  line `Provided that this sub-section shall not apply in a case where such amount is released during any`
  line `previous year at the closure of the account in circumstances specified in clauses ( b ), ( c ) and ( e ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ).`
  line `( 8 ) Where any asset acquired in accordance with the scheme 1 [or the deposit scheme] is sold or`
  line `otherwise transferred in any previous year by the assessee to any person at any time before the expiry of`
  line `eight years from the end of the previous year in which it was acquired, such part of the cost of such asset`
  line `as is relatable to the deduction allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to be the profits and gains`
  line `of business or profession of the previous year in which the asset is sold or otherwise transferred and shall`
  line `accordingly be chargeable to income-tax as the income of that previous year:`
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply —`
  line `( i ) where the asset is sold or otherwise transferred by the assessee to Government, a local`
  line `authority, a corporation established by or under a Central, State or Provincial Act or a Government`
  line `company as defined in section 617 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956); or`
  line `( ii ) where the sale or transfer of the asset is made in connection with the succession of a firm by a`
  line `company in the business or profession carried on by the firm as a result of which the firm sells or`
  line `otherwise transfers to the company any asset and the scheme 1 [or the deposit scheme] continues to`
  line `apply to the company in the manner applicable to the firm.`
  line `Explanation. — The provisions of clause ( ii ) of the proviso shall apply only where —`
  line `( i ) all the properties of the firm relating to the business or profession immediately before the`
  line `succession become the properties of the company;`
  line `( ii ) all the liabilities of the firm relating to the business or profession immediately before the`
  line `succession become the liabilities of the company; and`
  line `( iii ) all the shareholders of the company were partners of the firm immediately before the`
  line succession.
  line `( 9 ) The Central Government, if it considers necessary or expedient so to do, may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, direct that the deduction allowable under this section shall not be allowed after such`
  line `date as may be specified therein.`
  line `Explanation. — In this section, —`
  line `2 [( a ) “Coffee Board” means the Coffee Board constituted under section 4 of the Coffee`
  line `Act, 1942 (7 of 1942);`
  line `( aa ) “National Bank” means the National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development`
  line `established under section 3 of the National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development`
  line `Act, 1981 (61 of 1981);`
  line `( ab ) “Rubber Board” means the Rubber Board constit uted under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 4 of`
  line `the Rubber Act, 1947 (24 of 1947);]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 16, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_179:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-179
  sectionNo (179)
  orderNo 179
  title `Page 179`
  content obj_root_law_sections_179_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes
  sourcePage 179
obj_root_law_sections_179_content:
  string
  line 179
  line `( b ) “Tea Board” means the Tea Board established under section 4 of the Tea Act, 1953`
  line `(29 of 1953).]`
  line `1 [ 33ABA. Site Restoration Fund. — ( 1 ) Where an assessee is carrying on business consisting of the`
  line `prospecting for, or extraction or production of, petroleum or natural gas or both in India and in relation to`
  line `which the Central Government has entered into an agreement with such assessee for such business, has`
  line `before the end of the previous year —`
  line `( a ) deposited with the State Bank of India any amount or amounts in an account (hereafter in this`
  line `section referred to as the special account) maintained by the assessee with that Bank in accordance`
  line `with, and for the purposes specified in, a scheme (hereafter in this section referred to as the scheme)`
  line `approved in this behalf by the Government of India in the Ministry of Petroleum and Natural Gas; or`
  line `( b ) deposited any amount in an account (hereafter in this section referred to as the Site`
  line `Restoration Account) opened by the assessee in accordance with, and for the purposes specified in, a`
  line `scheme framed by the Ministry referred to in clause ( a ) (hereafter in this section referred to as the`
  line `deposit scheme),`
  line `the assessee shall, subject to the provisions of this section, be allowed a deduction (such deduction being`
  line `allowed before the loss, if any, brought forward from earlier years is set off under section 72) of —`
  line `( i ) a sum equal to the amount or the aggregate of the amounts so deposited; or`
  line `( ii ) a sum equal to twenty per cent. of the profits of such business (computed under the head`
  line `“Profits and gains of business or profession” before making any deduction under this section),`
  line `whichever is less:`
  line `Provided that where such assessee is a firm, or any association of persons or any body of individuals,`
  line `the deduction under this section shall not be allowed in the computation of the income of any partner or,`
  line `as the case may be, any member of such firm, association of persons or body of individuals:`
  line `Provided further that where any deduction, in respect of any amount deposited in the special account,`
  line `or in the Site Restoration Account, has been allowed under this sub-section in any previous year, no`
  line `deduction shall be allowed in respect of such amount in any other previous year:`
  line `Provided also that any amount credited in the special account or the Site Restoration Account by way`
  line `of interest shall be deemed to be a deposit.`
  line `( 2 ) The deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall not be admissible unless the accounts of such business`
  line `of the assessee for the previous year relevant to the assessment year for which the deduction is claimed`
  line `have been audited by an accountant as defined in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288`
  line `and the assessee furnishes, along with his return of income, the report of such audit in the prescribed form`
  line `duly signed and verified by such accountant:`
  line `Provided that in a case where the assessee is required by or under any other law to get his accounts`
  line `audited, it shall be sufficient compliance with the provisions of this sub-section if such assessee gets the`
  line `accounts of such business audited under such law and furnishes the report of the audit as required under`
  line `such other law and a further report in the form prescribed under this sub-section.`
  line `( 3 ) Any amount standing to the credit of the assessee in the special account or the Site Restoration`
  line `Account shall not be allowed to be withdrawn except for the purposes specified in the scheme or, as the`
  line `case may be, in the deposit scheme.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_180:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-180
  sectionNo (180)
  orderNo 180
  title `Page 180`
  content obj_root_law_sections_180_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes
  sourcePage 180
obj_root_law_sections_180_content:
  string
  line 180
  line `( 4 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 3 ), no deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall`
  line `be allowed in respect of any amount utilised for the purchase of —`
  line `( a ) any machinery or plant to be installed in any office premises or residential accommodation,`
  line `including any accommodation in the nature of a guest-house;`
  line `( b ) any office appliances (not being computers);`
  line `( c ) any machinery or plant, the whole of the actual cost of which is allowed as a deduction`
  line `(whether by way of depreciation or otherwise) in computing the income chargeable under the head`
  line `“Profits and gains of business or profession” of any one previous year;`
  line `( d ) any new machinery or plant to be installed in an industrial undertaking for the purposes of`
  line `business of construction, manufacture or production of any article or thing specified in the list in the`
  line `Eleventh Schedule.`
  line `( 5 ) Where any amount standing to the credit of the assessee in the special account or in the Site`
  line `Restoration Account is withdrawn on closure of the account during any previous year by the assessee, the`
  line `amount so withdrawn from the account, as reduced by the amount, if any, payable to the Central`
  line `Government by way of profit or production share as provided in the agreement referred to in section 42,`
  line `shall be deemed to be the profits and gains of business or profession of that previous year and shall`
  line `accordingly be chargeable to income-tax as the income of that previous year.`
  line `Explanation. — Where any amount is withdrawn on closure of the account in a previous year in which`
  line `the business carried on by the assessee is no longer in existence, the provisions of this sub-section shall`
  line `apply as if the business is in existence in that previous year.`
  line `( 6 ) Where any amount standing to the credit of the assessee in the special account or in the Site`
  line `Restoration Account is utilised by the assessee for the purposes of any expenditure in connection with`
  line `such business in accordance with the scheme or the deposit scheme, such expenditure shall not be allowed`
  line `in computing the income chargeable under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession”.`
  line `( 7 ) Where any amount, standing to the credit of the assessee in the special account or in the Site`
  line `Restoration Account, which is released during any previous year by the State Bank of India or which is`
  line `withdrawn by the assessee from the Site Restoration Account for being utilised by the assessee for the`
  line `purposes of such business in accordance with the scheme or the deposit scheme is not so utilised, either`
  line `wholly or in part, within that previous year, the whole of such amount or, as the case may be, part thereof`
  line `which is not so utilised shall be deemed to be profits and gains of business and accordingly chargeable to`
  line `income-tax as the income of that previous year.`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `( 8 ) Where any asset acquired in accordance with the scheme or the deposit scheme is sold or`
  line `otherwise transferred in any previous year by the assessee to any person at any time before the expiry of`
  line `eight years from the end of the previous year in which it was acquired, such part of the cost of such asset`
  line `as is relatable to the deduction allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to be the profits and gains`
  line `of business or profession of the previous year in which the asset is sold or otherwise transferred and shall`
  line `accordingly be chargeable to income-tax as the income of that previous year:`
  line `1. The proviso omitted by Act 27 of 1999, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes:
