  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes
  sourcePage 181
obj_root_law_sections_181_content:
  string
  line 181
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply —`
  line `( i ) where the asset is sold or otherwise transferred by the assessee to Government, a local`
  line `authority, a corporation established by or under a Central, State or Provincial Act or a Government`
  line `company as defined in section 617 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956); or`
  line `( ii ) where the sale or transfer of the asset is made in connection with the succession of a firm by`
  line `a company in the business or profession carried on by the firm as a result of which the firm sells or`
  line `otherwise transfers to the company any asset and the scheme or the deposit scheme continues to apply`
  line `to the company in the manner applicable to the firm.`
  line `Explanation. — The provisions of clause (ii) of the proviso shall apply only where —`
  line `( i ) all the properties of the firm relating to the business or profession immediately before the`
  line `succession become the properties of the company;`
  line `( ii ) all the liabilities of the firm relating to the business or profession immediately before the`
  line `succession become the liabilities of the company; and`
  line `( iii ) all the shareholders of the company were partners of the firm immediately before the`
  line succession.
  line `( 9 ) The Central Government may, if it considers necessary or expedient so to do, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, direct that the deduction allowable under this section shall not be allowed after such`
  line `date as may be specified therein.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “State Bank of India” means the State Bank of India constituted under the State Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1955 (23 of 1955);`
  line `( b ) the expression “amount standing to the credit of the assessee in the special account or the Site`
  line `Restoration Account” includes interest accru ed to such accounts.]`
  line `1 [ 33AC. Reserves for shipping business. — ( 1 ) 2 [In the case of an assessee, being a Government`
  line `company or a public company formed and registered in India with the main object of carrying on the`
  line `business of operation of ships, there shall, in accordance with and subject to the provisions of this section,`
  line `be allowed a deduction of an amount not exceeding fifty per cent. of profits derived from the business of`
  line `operation of ships (computed under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession” and before`
  line `making any deduction under this section), as is debited to the profit and loss account of the previous year`
  line `in respect of which the deduction is to be allowed and credited to a reserve account, to be utilised in the`
  line `manner laid down in sub-section ( 2 ):]`
  line `3 [Provided that where the aggregate of the amounts carried to such reserve account from time to time`
  line `exceeds twice the aggregate of the amounts of the paid-up share capital, the general reserves and amount`
  line `credited to the share premium account of the assessee, no allowance under this sub-section shall be made`
  line `in respect of such excess:]`
  line `4 [Provided further that for five assessment years commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 2001`
  line `and ending before the 1st day of April, 2006, the provisions of this sub-section shall have effect as if for`
  line `the wor ds “an amount not exceeding fifty per cent.. of profits”, the words “an amount not exceeding the`
  line `profits” had been substituted:]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 36 of 1989, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 8, for certain words, brackets and figures (w.e.f. 1-4-1996).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 15, for the first proviso (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
