  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes
  sourcePage 183
obj_root_law_sections_183_content:
  string
  line 183
  line `1 [( aa ) “ Government company ” shall have the meani ng assigned to it in section 617 of the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);]`
  line `( b ) “new ship” shall have the same meaning as in clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 32AB.]`
  line `2 [ 33B. Rehabilitation allowance. — Where the business of any industrial undertaking carried on in`
  line `India is discontinued in any previous year by reason of extensive damage to, or destruction of, any`
  line `building, machinery, plant or furniture owned by the assessee and used for the purposes of such business`
  line `as a direct result of —`
  line `( i ) flood, typhoon, hurricane, cyclone, earthquake or other convulsion of nature; or`
  line `( ii ) riot or civil disturbance; or`
  line `( iii ) accidental fire or explosion; or`
  line `( iv ) action by an enemy or action taken in combating an enemy (whether with or without a`
  line `declaration of war),`
  line `and, thereafter, at any time before the expiry of three years from the end of such previous year, the`
  line `business is re-established, reconstructed or revived by the assessee, he shall, in respect of the previous`
  line `year in which the business is so re-established, reconstructed or revived, be allowed a deduction of a sum`
  line `by way of rehabilitation allowance equivalent to sixty per cent.. of the amount of the deduction allowable`
  line `to him under clause ( iii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 32in respect of the building, machinery, plant or`
  line `furniture so damaged or destroyed:`
  line `3 [Provided that no deduction under this section shall be allowed in relation to the assessment year`
  line `commencing on the 1st day of April, 1985, or any subsequent assessment year.]`
  line `Explanation. — In this sect ion, “industrial undertaking” means any undertaking which is mainly`
  line `engaged in the business of generation or distribution of electricity or any other form of power or in the`
  line `construction of ships or in the manufacture or processing of goods or in mining.]`
  line `34. Conditions for depreciation allowance and development rebate. — 4 * * * * *`
  line `( 3 ) ( a ) The deduction referred to in section 33 shall not be allowed unless an amount equal to`
  line `seventy-five per cent.. of the development rebate to be actually allowed is debited to the profit and loss`
  line `account of 5 [any previous year in respect of which the deduction is to be allowed under sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `that section or any earlier previous year (being a previous year not earlier than the year in which the ship`
  line `was acquired or the machinery or plant was installed or the ship, machinery or plant was first put to use)]`
  line `and credited to a reserve account to be utilised by the assessee during a period of eight years next`
  line `following for the purposes of the business of the undertaking, other than —`
  line `( i ) for distribution by way of dividends or profits; or`
  line `( ii ) for remittance outside India as profits or for the creation of any asset outside India:`
  line `Provided that this clause shall not apply where the assessee is a company, being a licensee within`
  line `the meaning of the Electricity (Supply) Act, 1948 (54 of 1948), or where the ship has been acquired`
  line `or the machinery or plant has been installed before the 1st day of January, 1958:`
  line `6 [Provided further that where a ship has been acquired after the 28th day of February, 1966, this`
  line `clause shall have effect in respect of such ship as if for the words “seventy - five”, the word “fifty” had`
  line `been substituted.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1967).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `4. Sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) omitted by 46 of 1986, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 11, for “the relevant previous year” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1962).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 13 of 1966, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-1966).`
