  content obj_root_law_sections_184_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes
  sourcePage 184
obj_root_law_sections_184_content:
  string
  line 184
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `( b ) If any ship, machinery or plant is sold or otherwise transferred by the assessee to any person at`
  line `any time before the expiry of eight years from the end of the previous year in which it was acquired or`
  line `installed, any allowance made under section 33or under the corresponding provisions of the Indian`
  line `Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922), in respect of that ship, machinery or plant shall be deemed to have`
  line `been wrongly made for the purposes of this Act, and the provisions of sub-section ( 5 ) of section 155shall`
  line `apply accordingly:`
  line `Provided that this clause shall not apply —`
  line `( i ) where the ship has been acquired or the machinery or plant has been installed before the 1st`
  line `day of January, 1958; or`
  line `( ii ) where the ship, machinery or plant is sold or otherwise transferred by the assessee to the`
  line `Government, a local authority, a corporation established by a Central, State or Provincial Act or a`
  line `Government company as defined in section 617 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956); or`
  line `( iii ) where the sale or transfer of the ship, machinery or plant is made in connection with the`
  line `amalgamation or succession, referred to in sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 4 ) of section 33.`
  line `2 [ 34A. Restriction on unabsorbed depreciation and unabsorbed investment allowance for`
  line `limited period in case of certain domestic companies. — ( 1 ) In computing the profits and gains of the`
  line `business of a domestic company in relation to the previous year relevant to the assessment year`
  line `commencing on the 1st day of April, 1992, where effect is to be given to the unabsorbed depreciation`
  line `allowance or unabsorbed investment allowance or both in relation to any previous year relevant to the`
  line `assessment year commencing on or before the 1st day of April, 1991, the deduction shall be restricted to`
  line `two-third of such allowance or allowances and the balance, —`
  line `( a ) where it relates to depreciation allowance, be added to the depreciation allowance for the`
  line `previous year relevant to the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1993 and be`
  line `deemed to be part of that allowance or if there is no such allowance for that previous year, be deemed`
  line `to be the allowance for that previous year and so on for the succeeding previous years;`
  line `( b ) where it relates to investment allowance, be carried forward to the assessment year`
  line `commencing on the 1st day of April, 1993 and the balance of the investment allowance, if any, still`
  line `outstanding shall be carried forward to the following assessment year and where the period of eight`
  line `years has expired before the portion of such balance is adjusted, the said period shall be extended`
  line `beyond eight years till such time the portion of the said balance is absorbed in the profits and gains of`
  line `the business of the domestic company.`
  line `( 2 ) For the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1992, the provisions of`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 32 and sub-section ( 3 ) of section 32Ashall apply to the extent such provisions`
  line `are not inconsistent with the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) of this section.`
  line `( 3 ) Nothing contained in sub-section ( 1 ) shall apply where the amount of unabsorbed depreciation`
  line `allowance or of the unabsorbed investment allowance, as the case may be, or the aggregate amount of`
  line `such allowances in the case of a domestic company is less than one lakh rupees.`
  line `( 4 ) Nothing contained in sections 234B and 234Cshall apply to any shortfall in the payment of any`
  line `tax due on the assessed tax or, as the case may be, returned income where such shortfall is on account of`
  line `restricting the amount of depreciation allowance or investment allowance under this section and the`
  line `assessee has paid the amount of shortfall before furnishing the return of income under sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 139.]`
  line `1. The Explanation omitted by Act 12 of 1990, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
