obj_root_law_sections_187_content:
  string
  line 187
  line `1 [Provided also that where an application under the first proviso is made on or after the date on which`
  line `the Taxation Laws (Amendment) Bill, 2006 receives the assent of the President, every notification under`
  line `clause ( ii ) or clause ( iii ) shall be issued or an order rejecting the application shall be passed within the`
  line `period of twelve months from the end of the month in which such application was received by the Central`
  line Government.]
  line `( 2 ) For the purposes of clause ( iv ) of sub-section ( 1 ), —`
  line `2 [( i ) in a case where such capital expenditure is incurred before the 1st day of April, 1967,`
  line `one-fifth of the capital expenditure incurred in any previous year shall be deducted for that previous`
  line `year; and the balance of the expenditure shall be deducted in equal instalments for each of the four`
  line `immediately succeeding previous years;`
  line `( ia ) in a case where such capital expenditure is incurred after the 31st day of March, 1967, the`
  line `whole of such capital expenditure incurred in any previous year shall be deducted for that previous`
  line `year:]`
  line `3 [Provided that no deduction shall be admissible under this clause in respect of any expenditure`
  line `incurred on the acquisition of any land, whether the land is acquired as such or as part of any`
  line `property, after the 29th day of February, 1984.]`
  line `4 [ Explanation 1]. — Where any capital expenditure has been incurred before the commencement`
  line `of the business, the aggregate of the expenditure so incurred within the three years immediately`
  line `preceding the commencement of the business shall be deemed to have been incurred in the previous`
  line `year in which the business is commenced.`
  line `3 [ Explanation 2. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( a ) “land” includes any in terest in land; and`
  line `( b ) the acquisition of any land shall be deemed to have been made by the assessee on the date`
  line `on which the instrument of transfer of such land to him has been registered under the Registration`
  line `Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), or where he has taken or retained the possession of such land or any part`
  line `thereof in part performance of a contract of the nature referred to in section 53A of the Transfer`
  line `of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882), the date on which he has so taken or retained possession of`
  line `such land or part;]`
  line `( ii ) notwithstanding anything contained in clause ( i ), where an asset representing expenditure of a`
  line `capital nature 5 [incurred before the 1st day of April, 1967], ceases to be used in a previous year for`
  line `scientific research related to the business and the value of the asset at the time of the cessation,`
  line `together with the aggregate of deductions already allowed under clause ( i ) falls short of the said`
  line `expenditure, then —`
  line `( a ) there shall be allowed a deduction for that previous year of an amount equal to such`
  line `deficiency, and`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 33 and the Third Schedule, for clause ( i ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1968).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-1984).`
  line `4. The Explanation numbered as Explanation 1 by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1984).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 33 and the Third Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-1968).`
