obj_root_law_sections_189_content:
  string
  line 189
  line `( b ) no deduction in respect of such sum shall be allowed under any other provision of this Act:`
  line `1 [Provided that the prescribed authority shall, before granting approval, satisfy itself about the`
  line `feasibility of carrying out the scientific research and shall submit its report to the 2 [Principal Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Chief Commissioner or] 3 [Principal Director General or Director General] in such form`
  line `as may be prescribed.]`
  line `4 [Provided further that where any sum is paid to such National Laboratory or university or Indian`
  line `Institute of Technology or specified person in a previous year relevant to the assessment year beginning`
  line `on or after the 1st day of April, 2021, the deduction under this sub-section shall be equal to the sum so`
  line paid.]
  line `5 [ Explanation 1. — The deduction, to which the assessee is entitled in respect of any sum paid to a`
  line `National Laboratory, University, Indian Institute of Technology or a specified person for the approved`
  line `programme referred to in this sub-section, shall not be denied merely on the ground that, subsequent to`
  line `the payment of such sum by the assessee, the approval granted to, —`
  line `( a ) such Laboratory, or specified person has been withdrawn; or`
  line `( b ) the programme, undertaken by the National Laboratory, University, Indian Institute of`
  line `Technology or specified person, has been withdrawn.]`
  line `6 [ 7 [ Explanation 2]. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “National Laboratory” means a scientific laboratory functioning at the national level under`
  line `the aegis of the Indian Council of Agricultural Research, the Indian Council of Medical Research, the`
  line `Council of Scientific and Industrial Research, the Defence Research and Development Organisation,`
  line `the Department of Electronics, the Department of Bio-Technology or the Department of Atomic`
  line `Energy and which is approved as a National Laboratory by the prescribed authority in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed;`
  line `( b ) “University” shall have the same meaning as in Explanation to clause ( ix ) of section 47;`
  line `( c ) “Indian Institute of Technology” shall have the same meaning as that of “Institute” in`
  line `clause ( g ) of section 3 of the Institutes of Technology Act, 1961 (59 of 1961);]`
  line `8 [( d ) “specified person” means such person as is approved by the prescribed authority.]`
  line `9 [( 2AB ) ( 1 ) Where a company 10 [engaged in the business of bio-technology or in 11 [any business of`
  line `manufacture or production of any article or thing, not being an article or thing specified in the list of the`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 12, for the provisos (w.e.f. 1-10-1996).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Director General” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `5. The Explanation inserted by Act 29 of 2006, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 13, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
  line `7. The Explanation renumbered as Explanation 2 thereof by Act 29 of 2006, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 23, for “engaged in the business of” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2002).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 12, for “the business of manufacture or production of any drugs, pharmaceuticals, electronic`
  line `equipments, computers, telecommunication equipments, chemicals or any other article or thing notified by the Board”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
