  string
  line 190
  line `Eleventh Schedule]] incurs any expenditure on scientific research (not being expenditure in the nature of`
  line `cost of any land or building) on in-house research and development facility as approved by the prescribed`
  line `authority, then, there shall be allowed a deduction of 1 [a sum equal to 2 [one and one-half times] of the`
  line `expenditure] so incurred.`
  line `3 [Provided that where such expenditure on scientific research (not being expenditure in the nature of`
  line `cost of any land or building) on in-house research and development facility is incurred in a previous year`
  line `relevant to the assessment year beginning on or after the 1st day of April, 2021, the deduction under this`
  line `clause shall be equal to the expenditure so incurred.]`
  line `4 [ Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, “expenditure on scientific research”, in relation to`
  line `drugs and pharmaceuticals, shall include expenditure incurred on clinical drug trial, obtaining approval`
  line `from any regulatory authority under any Central, State or Provincial Act and filing an application for a`
  line `patent under the Patents Act, 1970 (39 of 1970).]`
  line `( 2 ) No deduction shall be allowed in respect of the expenditure mentioned in clause ( 1 ) under any`
  line `other provision of this Act.`
  line `( 3 ) No company shall be entitled for deduction under clause ( 1 ) unless it enters into an agreement`
  line `with the prescribed authority for co-operation in such research and development facility and 5 [fulfils such`
  line `conditions with regard to maintenance of accounts and audit thereof and furnishing of reports in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed].`
  line `( 4 ) The prescribed authority shall submit its report in relation to the approval of the said facility to`
  line `the 6 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner or] 7 [Principal Director General or Director`
  line `General] in such form and within such time as may be prescribed.]`
  line `8 * * * * *`
  line `9 [( 6 ) No deduction shall be allowed to a company approved under sub-clause ( C ) of clause ( iia ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) in respect of the expenditure referred to in clause ( 1 ) which is incurred after the 31st day`
  line `of March, 2008.]`
  line `10 [( 2B ) ( a ) 11 [Where, before the 1st day of March, 1984, an assessee has incurred any expenditure]`
  line `(not being in the nature of capital expenditure incurred on the acquisition of any land or building or`
  line `construction of any building) on scientific research undertaken under a programme approved in this`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 16, for “a sum equal to one and one - fourth times of the expenditure” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2001).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 15 for “ two times ” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2018).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 12, for “for audit of accounts maintained for that facility” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2016).`
  line `6. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Director General” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `8. Clause ( 5 ) omitted by Act 28 of 2016, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-9-1980).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 6, for “Where an assessee has incurred any expenditure” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1984).`
