obj_root_law_sections_191_content:
  string
  line 191
  line `behalf by the prescribed authority having regard to the social, economic and industrial needs of India, he`
  line `shall, subject to the provisions of this sub-section, be allowed a deduction of a sum equal to one and`
  line `one-fourth times the amount of the expenditure certified by the prescribed authority to have been so`
  line `incurred during the previous year.`
  line `( b ) Where a deduction has been allowed under clause ( a ) for any previous year in respect of any`
  line `expenditure, no deduction in respect of such expenditure shall be allowed under clause ( i ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) or clause ( ia ) of sub-section ( 2 ) for the same or any other previous year.`
  line `( c ) Where a deduction is allowed for any previous year under this sub-section in respect of`
  line `expenditure represented wholly or partly by an asset, no deduction shall be allowed in respect of that asset`
  line `under 1 [clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 1 )] of section 32 for the same or any subsequent previous year.`
  line `( d ) Any deduction made under this sub-section in respect of any expenditure on scientific research in`
  line `excess of the expenditure actually incurred shall be deemed to have been wrongly made for the purposes`
  line `of this Act if the assessee fails to furnish within one year of the period allowed by the prescribed authority`
  line `for completion of the programme, a certificate of its completion obtained from that authority, and the`
  line `provisions of sub-section ( 5B ) of section 155 shall apply accordingly.]`
  line `2 [( 3 ) If any question arises under this section as to whether, and if so, to what extent, any activity`
  line `constitutes or constituted, or any asset is or was being used for, scientific research, the Board shall refer`
  line `the question to —`
  line `( a ) the Central Government, when such question relates to any activity under clauses ( ii ) and ( iii )`
  line `of sub-section ( 1 ), and its decision shall be final;`
  line `( b ) the prescribed authority, when such question relates to any activity other than the activity`
  line `specified in clause ( a ), whose decision shall be final.]`
  line `( 4 ) The provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 32shall apply in relation to deductions allowable`
  line `under clause ( iv ) of sub-section ( 1 ) as they apply in relation to deductions allowable in respect of`
  line depreciation.
  line `3 [( 5 ) Where, in a scheme of amalgamation, the amalgamating company sells or otherwise transfers to`
  line `the amalgamated company (being an Indian company) any asset representing expenditure of a capital`
  line `nature on scientific research, —`
  line `( i ) the amalgamating company shall not be allowed the deduction under clause ( ii ) or clause ( iii )`
  line `of sub-section ( 2 ); and`
  line `( ii ) the provisions of this section shall, as far as may be, apply to the amalgamated company as`
  line `they would have applied to the amalgamating company if the latter had not so sold or otherwise`
  line `transferred the asset.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 32, for “clauses ( i ), ( ii ), ( iia ) and ( iii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) or under sub-section ( 1A )”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 15, for sub-section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-1967).`
