obj_root_law_sections_192:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-192
  sectionNo (192)
  orderNo 192
  title `Page 192`
  content obj_root_law_sections_192_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes
  sourcePage 192
obj_root_law_sections_192_content:
  string
  line 192
  line `1 [35A. Expenditure on acquisition of patent rights or copyrights. — ( 1 ) In respect of any`
  line `expenditure of a capital nature incurred after the 28th day of February, 1966 2 [but before the 1st day of`
  line `April, 1998], on the acquisition of patent rights or copyrights (hereafter, in this section, referred to as`
  line `rights) used for the purposes of the business, there shall, subject to and in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of this section, be allowed for each of the relevant previous years, a deduction equal to the appropriate`
  line `fraction of the amount of such expenditure.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “relevant previous years” means the fourteen previous years beginning with the previous year`
  line `in which such expenditure is incurred or, where such expenditure is incurred before the`
  line `commencement of the business, the fourteen previous years beginning with the previous year in`
  line `which the business commenced:`
  line `Provided that where the rights commenced, that is to say, became effective, in any year prior to`
  line `the previous year in which expenditure on the acquisition thereof was incurred by the assessee, this`
  line `clause shall have effect with the substitution for the reference to fourteen years of a reference to`
  line `fourteen years less the number of complete years which, when the rights are acquired by the assessee,`
  line `have elapsed since the commencement thereof, and if fourteen years have elapsed as aforesaid, of a`
  line `reference to one year;`
  line `( ii ) “appropriate fraction” means the fraction the numerator of which is one and the denominator`
  line `of which is the number of the relevant previous years.`
  line `( 2 ) Where the rights come to an end without being subsequently revived or where the whole or any`
  line `part of the rights is sold and the proceeds of the sale (so far as they consist of capital sums) are not less`
  line `than the cost of acquisition thereof remaining unallowed, no deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be`
  line `allowed in respect of the previous year in which the rights come to an end or, as the case may be, the`
  line `whole or any part of the rights is sold or in respect of any subsequent previous year.`
  line `( 3 ) Where the rights either come to an end without being subsequently revived or are sold in their`
  line `entirety and the proceeds of the sale (so far as they consist of capital sums) are less than the cost of`
  line `acquisition thereof remaining unallowed, a deduction equal to such cost remaining unallowed or, as the`
  line `case may be, such cost remaining unallowed as reduced by the proceeds of the sale, shall be allowed in`
  line `respect of the previous year in which the rights come to an end, or, as the case may be, are sold.]`
  line `( 4 ) Where the whole or any part of the rights is sold and the proceeds of the sale (so far as they`
  line `consist of capital sums) exceed the amount of the cost of acquisition thereof remaining unallowed, so`
  line `much of the excess as does not exceed the difference between the cost of acquisition of the rights and the`
  line `amount of such cost remaining unallowed shall be chargeable to income-tax as income of the business of`
  line `the previous year in which the whole or any part of the rights is sold.`
  line `Explanation. — Where the whole or any part of the rights is sold in a previous year in which the`
  line `business is no longer in existence, the provisions of this sub-section shall apply as if the business is in`
  line `existence in that previous year.`
  line `( 5 ) Where a part of the rights is sold and sub-section ( 4 ) does not apply, the amount of the deduction`
  line `to be allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be arrived at by —`
  line `( a ) subtracting the proceeds of the sale (so far as they consist of capital sums) from the amount`
  line `of the cost of acquisition of the rights remaining unallowed; and`
  line `( b ) dividing the remainder by the number of relevant previous years which have not expired at`
  line `the beginning of the previous year during which the rights are sold.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1966, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-1966).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
