obj_root_law_sections_193_content:
  string
  line 193
  line `1 [( 6 ) Where, in a scheme of amalgamation, the amalgamating company sells or otherwise transfers`
  line `the rights to the amalgamated company (being an Indian company), —`
  line `( i ) the provisions of sub-sections ( 3 ) and ( 4 ) shall not apply in the case of the amalgamating`
  line `company; and`
  line `( ii ) the provisions of this section shall, as far as may be, apply to the amalgamated company as`
  line `they would have applied to the amalgamating company if the latter had not so sold or otherwise`
  line `transferred the rights.]`
  line `2 [( 7 ) Where in a scheme of demerger, the demerged company sells or otherwise transfers the rights to`
  line `the resulting company (being an Indian company), —`
  line `( i ) the provisions of sub-sections ( 3 ) and ( 4 ) shall not apply in the case of the demerged`
  line `company; and`
  line `( ii ) the provisions of this section shall, as far as may be, apply to the resulting company as they`
  line `would have applied to the demerged company, if the latter had not sold or otherwise transferred the`
  line rights.]
  line `3 [35AB. Expenditure on know-how. — ( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ), where the`
  line `assessee has paid 4 [in any previous year relevant to the assessment year commencing on or before the`
  line `1st day of April, 1998] any lump sum consideration for acquiring any know-how for use for the purposes`
  line `of his business, one-sixth of the amount so paid shall be deducted in computing the profits and gains of`
  line `the business for that previous year, and the balance amount shall be deducted in equal instalments for`
  line `each of the five immediately succeeding previous years.`
  line `( 2 ) Where the know-how referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) is developed in a laboratory, university or`
  line `institution referred to in sub-section ( 2B ) of section 32A, one-third of the said lump sum consideration`
  line `paid in the previous year by the assessee shall be deducted in computing the profits and gains of the`
  line `business for that year, and the balance amount shall be deducted in equal instalments for each of the two`
  line `immediately succeeding previous years.`
  line `5 [( 3 ) Where there is a transfer of an undertaking under a scheme of amalgamation or demerger and`
  line `the amalgamating or the demerged company is entitled to a deduction under this section, then, the`
  line `amalgamated company or the resulting company, as the case may be, shall be entitled to claim deduction`
  line `under this section in respect of such undertaking to the same extent and in respect of the residual period as`
  line `it would have been allowable to the amalgamating company or the demerged company, as the case may`
  line `be, had such amalgamation or demerger not taken place.]`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, “know - how” means any industrial information or`
  line `technique likely to assist in the manufacture or processing of goods or in the working of a mine, oil well`
  line `or other sources of mineral deposits (including the searching for, discovery or testing of deposits or the`
  line `winning of access thereto).]`
  line `6 [35ABA. Expenditure for obtaining right to use spectrum for telecommunication services. — ( 1 )`
  line `In respect of any expenditure, being in the nature of capital expenditure, incurred for acquiring any right`
  line `to use spectrum for telecommunication services either before the commencement of the business or`
  line `thereafter at any time during any previous year and for which payment has actually been made to obtain a`
  line `right to use spectrum, there shall, subject to and in accordance with the provisions of this section, be`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 1967, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-1967).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 32 of 1985, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-1986).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 12, for “in any previous year” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1999).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
