obj_root_law_sections_194_content:
  string
  line 194
  line `allowed for each of the relevant previous years, a deduction equal to the appropriate fraction of the`
  line `amount of such expenditure.`
  line `( 2 ) The provisions contained in sub-sections ( 2 ) to ( 8 ) of section 35 ABB, shall apply as if for the`
  line `word “licence”, the word “spectrum” had been substituted.`
  line `( 3 ) Where, in a previous year, any deduction has been claimed and granted to the assessee under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ), and, subsequently, there is failure to comply with any of the provisions of this section,`
  line `then, —`
  line `( a ) the deduction shall be deemed to have been wrongly allowed;`
  line `( b ) the Assessing Officer may, notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, re-compute the`
  line `total income of the assessee for the said previous year and make the necessary rectification;`
  line `( c ) the provisions of section 154 shall, so far as may be, apply and the period of four years`
  line `specified in sub-section ( 7 ) of that section being reckoned from the end of the previous year in which`
  line `the failure to comply with the provisions of this section takes place.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “relevant previous years” means,—`
  line `( A ) in a case where the spectrum fee is actually paid before the commencement of the business to`
  line `operate telecommunication services, the previous years beginning with the previous year in which`
  line `such business commenced;`
  line `( B ) in any other case, the previous years beginning with the previous year in which the spectrum`
  line `fee is actually paid,`
  line `and the subsequent previous year or years during which the spectrum, for which the fee is paid,`
  line `shall be in force;`
  line `( ii ) “appropriate fraction” means the fraction, the numerator of wh ich is one and the denominator of`
  line `which is the total number of the relevant previous years;`
  line `( iii ) “payment has actually been made” means the actual payment of expenditure irrespective of the`
  line `previous year in which the liability for the expenditure was incurred according to the method of`
  line `accounting regularly employed by the assessee or payable in such manner as may be prescribed.]`
  line `1 [35ABB. Expenditure for obtaining licence to operate telecommunication services. — ( 1 ) In`
  line `respect of any expenditure, being in the nature of capital expenditure, incurred 2 [for acquiring any right to`
  line `operate telecommunication services either before the commencement of the business to operate`
  line `telecommunication services or thereafter at any time during any previous year] and for which payment`
  line `has actually been made to obtain a licence, there shall, subject to and in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `this section, be allowed for each of the relevant previous years, a deduction equal to the appropriate`
  line `fraction of the amount of such expenditure.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `3 [( i ) “relevant previous years” means,—`
  line `( A ) in a case where the licence fee is actually paid before the commencement of the business`
  line `to operate telecommunication services, the previous years beginning with the previous year in`
  line `which such business commenced;`
  line `( B ) in any other case, the previous years beginning with the previous year in which the`
  line `licence fee is actually paid,`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-1996).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 18, for “for acquiring any right to operate telecommunication services” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1996).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 18, for clause ( i ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1996).`
