obj_root_law_sections_195_content:
  string
  line 195
  line `and the subsequent previous year or years during which the licence, for which the fee is paid, shall be in`
  line force;]
  line `( ii ) “appropriate fraction” means the fraction the numerator of which is one and the denominator`
  line `of which is the total number of the relevant previous years;`
  line `( iii ) “payment has actually been made” means the act ual payment of expenditure irrespective of`
  line `the previous year in which the liability for the expenditure was incurred according to the method of`
  line `accounting regularly employed by the assessee.`
  line `( 2 ) Where the licence is transferred and the proceeds of the transfer (so far as they consist of capital`
  line `sums) are less than the expenditure incurred remaining unallowed, a deduction equal to such expenditure`
  line `remaining unallowed, as reduced by the proceeds of the transfer, shall be allowed in respect of the`
  line `previous year in which the licence is transferred.`
  line `( 3 ) Where the whole or any part of the licence is transferred and the proceeds of the transfer (so far as`
  line `they consist of capital sums) exceed the amount of the expenditure incurred remaining unallowed, so`
  line `much of the excess as does not exceed the difference between the expenditure incurred to obtain the`
  line `licence and the amount of such expenditure remaining unallowed shall be chargeable to income-tax as`
  line `profits and gains of the business in the previous year in which the licence has been transferred.`
  line `Explanation. — Where the licence is transferred in a previous year in which the business is no longer`
  line `in existence, the provisions of this sub-section shall apply as if the business is in existence in that previous`
  line year.
  line `( 4 ) Where the whole or any part of the licence is transferred and the proceeds of the transfer (so far as`
  line `they consist of capital sums) are not less than the amount of expenditure incurred remaining unallowed,`
  line `no deduction for such expenditure shall be allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) in respect of the previous year in`
  line `which the licence is transferred or in respect of any subsequent previous year or years.`
  line `( 5 ) Where a part of the licence is transferred in a previous year and sub-section ( 3 ) does not apply, the`
  line `deduction to be allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) for expenditure incurred remaining unallowed shall be`
  line `arrived at by —`
  line `( a ) subtracting the proceeds of transfer (so far as they consist of capital sums) from the`
  line `expenditure remaining unallowed; and`
  line `( b ) dividing the remainder by the number of relevant previous years which have not expired at`
  line `the beginning of the previous year during which the licence is transferred.`
  line `( 6 ) Where, in a scheme of amalgamation, the amalgamating company sells or otherwise transfers the`
  line `licence to the amalgamated company (being an Indian company), —`
  line `( i ) the provisions of sub-sections ( 2 ), ( 3 ) and ( 4 ) shall not apply in the case of the amalgamating`
  line `company; and`
  line `( ii ) the provisions of this section shall, as far as may be, apply to the amalgamated company as`
  line `they would have applied to the amalgamating company if the latter had not transferred the licence.]`
  line `1 [( 7 ) Where, in a scheme of demerger, the demerged company sells or otherwise transfers the licence`
  line `to the resulting company (being an Indian company), —`
  line `( i ) the provisions of sub-sections ( 2 ), ( 3 ) and ( 4 ) shall not apply in the case of the demerged`
  line `company; and`
  line `( ii ) the provisions of this section shall, as far as may be, apply to the resulting company as they`
  line `would have applied to the demerged company if the latter had not transferred the licence.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
