obj_root_law_sections_196_content:
  string
  line 196
  line `1 [( 8 ) Where a deduction for any previous year under sub-section ( 1 ) is claimed and allowed in respect`
  line `of any expenditure referred to in that sub-section, no deduction shall be allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 32 for the same previous year or any subsequent previous year.]`
  line `2 [35AC. Expenditure on eligible projects or schemes. — ( 1 ) Where an assessee incurs any`
  line `expenditure by way of payment of any sum to a public sector company or a local authority or to an`
  line `association or institution approved by the National Committee for carrying out any eligible project or`
  line `scheme, the assessee shall, subject to the provisions of this section, be allowed a deduction of the amount`
  line `of such expenditure incurred during the previous year:`
  line `Provided that a company may, for claiming the deduction under this sub-section, incur expenditure`
  line `either by way of payment of any sum as aforesaid or directly on the eligible project or scheme.`
  line `( 2 ) The deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall not be allowed unless the assessee furnishes along with`
  line `his return of income a certificate —`
  line `( a ) where the payment is to a public sector company or a local authority or an association or`
  line `institution referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), from such public sector company or local authority or, as the`
  line `case may be, association or institution;`
  line `( b ) in any other case, from an accountant, as defined in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 288,`
  line `in such form, manner and containing such particulars (including particulars relating to the progress in`
  line `the work relating to the eligible project or scheme during the previous year) as may be prescribed.`
  line `3 [ Explanation. — The deduction, to which the assessee is entitled in respect of any sum paid to a`
  line `public sector company or a local authority or to an association or institution for carrying out the eligible`
  line `project or scheme referred to in this section applies, shall not be denied merely on the ground that`
  line `subsequent to the payment of such sum by the assessee, —`
  line `( a ) the approval granted to such association or institution has been withdrawn; or`
  line `( b ) the notification notifying the eligible project or scheme carried out by the public sector`
  line `company or local authority or association or institution has been withdrawn.]`
  line `( 3 ) Where a deduction under this section is claimed and allowed for any assessment year in respect of`
  line `any expenditure referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), deduction shall not be allowed in respect of such`
  line `expenditure under any other provision of this Act for the same or any other assessment year.`
  line `4 [( 4 ) Where an association or institution is approved by the National Committee under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ), and subsequently —`
  line `( i ) that Committee is satisfied that the project or the scheme is not being carried on in accordance`
  line `with all or any of the conditions subject to which approval was granted; or`
  line `( ii ) such association or institution, to which approval has been granted, has not furnished to the`
  line `National Committee, after the end of each financial year, a report in such form and setting forth such`
  line `particulars and within such time as may be prescribed`
  line `the National Committee may, at any time, after giving a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against`
  line `the proposed withdrawal to the concerned association or institution, withdraw the approval:`
  line `Provided that a copy of the order withdrawing the approval shall be forwarded by the National`
  line `Committee to the Assessing Officer having jurisdiction over the concerned association or institution.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-1996).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `4. Subs by Act 23 of 2004, s. 10 for sub-section ( 4 ) (w.e.f. 1-10-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_197:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-197
  sectionNo (197)
  orderNo 197
  title `Page 197`
  content obj_root_law_sections_197_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes
  sourcePage 197
obj_root_law_sections_197_content:
  string
  line 197
  line `( 5 ) Where any project or scheme has been notified as an eligible project or scheme under clause ( b ) of`
  line `the Explanation, and subsequently —`
  line `( i ) the National Committee is satisfied that the project or the scheme is not being carried on in`
  line `accordance with all or any of the conditions subject to which such project or scheme was notified; or`
  line `( ii ) a report in respect of such eligible project or scheme has not been furnished after the end of`
  line `each financial year, in such form and setting forth such particulars and within such time as may be`
  line prescribed,
  line `such notification may be withdrawn in the same manner in which it was issued:`
  line `Provided that a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the proposed withdrawal shall be`
  line `given by the National Committee to the concerned association, institution, public sector company or local`
  line `authority, as the case may be:`
  line `Provided further that a copy of the notification by which the notification of the eligible project or`
  line `scheme is withdrawn shall be forwarded to the Assessing Officer having jurisdiction over the concerned`
  line `association, institution, public sector company or local authority, as the case may be, carrying on such`
  line `eligible project or scheme.]`
  line `1 [( 6 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, where —`
  line `( i ) the approval of the National Committee, granted to an association or institution, is withdrawn`
  line `under sub-section ( 4 ) or the notification in respect of eligible project or scheme is withdrawn in the`
  line `case of a public sector company or local authority or an association or institution under`
  line `sub-section ( 5 ); or`
  line `( ii ) a company has claimed deduction under the proviso to sub-section ( 1 ) in respect of any`
  line `expenditure incurred directly on the eligible project or scheme and the approval for such project or`
  line `scheme is withdrawn by the National Committee under sub-section ( 5 ),`
  line `the total amount of the payment received by the public sector company or the local authority or the`
  line `association or the institution, as the case may be, in respect of which such company or authority or`
  line `association or institution has furnished a certificate referred to in clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 2 ) or the`
  line `deduction claimed by a company under the proviso to sub-section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to be the income of`
  line `such company or authority or association or institution, as the case may be, for the previous year in which`
  line `such approval or notification is withdrawn and tax shall be charged on such income at the maximum`
  line `marginal rate in force for that year.]`
  line `2 [( 7 ) No deduction under this section shall be allowed in respect of any assessment year commencing`
  line `on or after the 1st day of April, 2018.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “National Committee” means the Com mittee constituted by the Central Government, from`
  line `amongst persons of eminence in public life, in accordance with the rules made under this Act;`
  line `( b ) “eligible project or scheme” means such project or scheme for promoting the social and`
  line `economic welfare of, or the uplift of, the public as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, specify in this behalf on the recommendations of the National Committee.]`
  line `3 [35AD. Deduction in respect of expenditure on specified business. — ( 1 ) An assessee shall be`
  line `allowed a deduction in respect of the whole of any expenditure of capital nature incurred, wholly and`
  line `exclusively, for the purposes of any specified business carried on by him during the previous year in`
  line `which such expenditure is incurred by him:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_198:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-198
  sectionNo (198)
  orderNo 198
  title `Page 198`
  content obj_root_law_sections_198_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes
  sourcePage 198
obj_root_law_sections_198_content:
  string
  line 198
  line `Provided that the expenditure incurred, wholly and exclusively, for the purposes of any specified`
  line `business, shall be allowed as deduction during the previous year in which he commences operations of his`
  line `specified business, if —`
  line `( a ) the expenditure is incurred prior to the commencement of its operations; and`
  line `( b ) the amount is capitalised in the books of account of the assessee on the date of`
  line `commencement of its operations.]`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `( 2 ) This section applies to the specified business which fulfils all the following conditions,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( i ) it is not set up by splitting up, or the reconstruction, of a business already in existence;`
  line `( ii ) it is not set up by the transfer to the specified business of machinery or plant previously used`
  line `for any purpose;`
  line `( iii ) where the business is of the nature referred to in sub-clause ( iii ) of clause ( c ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 8 ), such business, —`
  line `( a ) is owned by a company formed and registered in India under the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) or by a consortium of such companies or by an authority or a board or a`
  line `corporation established or constituted under any Central or State Act;`
  line `( b ) has been approved by the Petroleum and Natural Gas Regulatory Board established`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 3 of the Petroleum and Natural Gas Regulatory Board`
  line `Act, 2006 (19 of 2006) and notified by the Central Government in the Official Gazette in this`
  line behalf;
  line `( c ) has made not less than 2 [such proportion of its total pipeline capacity as specified by`
  line `regulations made by the Petroleum and Natural Gas Regulatory Board established under sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ) of section 3 of the Petroleum and Natural Gas Regulatory Board Act, 2006 (19 of`
  line `2006)] available for use on common carrier basis by any person other than the assessee or an`
  line `associated person; and`
  line `( d ) fulfils any other condition as may be prescribed.`
  line `3 [( iv ) where the business is of the nature referred to in sub-clause ( xiv ) of clause ( c ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 8 ), such business, —`
  line `( A ) is owned by a company registered in India or by a consortium of such companies or by an`
  line `authority or a board or corporation or any other body established or constituted under any Central`
  line `or State Act;`
  line `( B ) entity referred to in sub-clause ( A ) has entered into an agreement with the Central`
  line `Government or a State Government or a local authority or any other statutory body for`
  line `developing or operating and maintaining or developing, operating and maintaining, a new`
  line `infrastructure facility.]`
  line `4 [( 3 ) Where a deduction under this section is claimed and allowed in respect of the specified business`
  line `for any assessment year, no deduction shall be allowed under the provisions of 5 [section 10AA and]`
  line `1. Sub-section ( 1A ) Omitted by Act 28 of 2016, s. 18 (w.e.f 1-4-2018).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 10, for the words “one - third of its total pipeline capacity” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2010).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 10, for sub-section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2011).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_199:
