obj_root_law_sections_204_content:
  string
  line 204
  line `( b ) the training of persons for implementing any programme of rural development had been`
  line `started by the association or institution before the 1st day of March, 1983.]`
  line `1 [ Explanation. — The deduction, to which the assessee is entitled in respect of any sum paid to an`
  line `association or institution for carrying out the programme of rural development referred to in sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ), shall not be denied merely on the ground that subsequent to the payment of such sum by`
  line `the assessee, the approval granted to such programme of rural development, or as the case may be, to`
  line `the association or institution has been withdrawn.]`
  line `( 2B ) No certificate of the nature referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-section ( 2A ) shall be issued by`
  line `any association or institution unless such association or institution has obtained from the prescribed`
  line `authority authorisation in writing to issue certificates of such nature.]`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, “programme of rural development” shall have the`
  line `meaning assigned to it in the Explanation to sub-section ( 1 ) of section 35CC.`
  line `( 3 ) Where a deduction under this section is claimed and allowed for any assessment year in respect of`
  line `any expenditure referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), deduction shall not be allowed in respect of such`
  line `expenditure under section 35C or section 35CC or section 80G or any other provision of this Act for the`
  line `same or any other assessment year.]`
  line `2 [35CCB. Expenditure by way of payment to associations and institutions for carrying out`
  line `programmes of conservation of natural resources. — 3 [( 1 ) 4 [Where an assessee incurs any expenditure`
  line `on or before the 31st day of March, 2002] by way of payment of any sum —`
  line `( a ) to an association or institution, which has as its object the undertaking of any programme of`
  line `conservation of natural resources or of afforestation, to be used for carrying out any programme of`
  line `conservation of natural resources or afforestation approved by the prescribed authority; or`
  line `( b ) to such fund for afforestation as may be notified by the Central Government,`
  line `the assessee shall, subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ), be allowed a deduction of the amount of`
  line `such expenditure incurred during the previous year.]`
  line `( 2 ) The deduction under 5 [clause ( a ) of] sub-section ( 1 ) shall not be allowed with respect to`
  line `expenditure by way of payment of any sum to any association or institution, unless such association or`
  line `institution is for the time being approved in this behalf by the prescribed authority:`
  line `Provided that the prescribed authority shall not grant such approval for more than three years at a`
  line time.
  line `( 3 ) Where a deduction under this section is claimed and allowed for any assessment year in respect of`
  line `any expenditure referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), deduction shall not be allowed in respect of such`
  line `expenditure under any other provision of this Act for the same or any other assessment year.]`
  line `6 [ 35CCC. Expenditure on agricultural extension project. — ( 1 ) Where an assessee incurs any`
  line `expenditure on agricultural extension project notified by the Board in this behalf in accordance with`
  line `theguidelines as may be prescribed, then, there shall be allowed a deduction of a sum equal to one and`
  line `one-half times of such expenditure.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `2. Restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 earlier omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s.10 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Original s. 35CCB was inserted`
  line `by Act 14 of 1982, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-6-1982).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 12, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 17, for “Where an assessee incurs any expenditure” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2003).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
