obj_root_law_sections_206_content:
  string
  line 206
  line `( iii ) conducting market survey or any other survey necessary for the business of the assessee;`
  line `( iv ) engineering services relating to the business of the assessee:`
  line `Provided that the work in connection with the preparation of the feasibility report or the`
  line `project report or the conducting of market survey or of any other survey or the engineering`
  line `services referred to in this clause is carried out by the assessee himself or by a concern which is`
  line `for the time being approved in this behalf by the Board;`
  line `( b ) legal charges for drafting any agreement between the assessee and any other person for any`
  line `purpose relating to the setting up or conduct of the business of the assessee;`
  line `( c ) where the assessee is a company, also expenditure —`
  line `( i ) by way of legal charges for drafting the Memorandum and Articles of Association of the`
  line company;
  line `( ii ) on printing of the Memorandum and Articles of Association;`
  line `( iii ) by way of fees for registering the company under the provisions of the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line `( iv ) in connection with the issue, for public subscription, of shares in or debentures of the`
  line `company, being underwriting commission, brokerage and charges for drafting, typing, printing`
  line `and advertisement of the prospectus;`
  line `( d ) such other items of expenditure (not being expenditure eligible for any allowance or`
  line `deduction under any other provision of this Act) as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 3 ) Where the aggregate amount of the expenditure referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) exceeds an amount`
  line `calculated at two and one-half per cent —`
  line `( a ) of the cost of the project, or`
  line `( b ) where the assessee is an Indian company, at the option of the company, of the capital`
  line `employed in the business of the company,`
  line `the excess shall be ignored for the purpose of computing the deduction allowable under sub-section ( 1 ):`
  line `1 [Provided that where the aggregate amount of expenditure referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) is`
  line `incurred after the 31st day of March, 1998, the provisions of this sub-section shall have effect as if for`
  line `the words “two and one- half per cent”, the words “five per cent” had been substituted.]`
  line `Explanation. — In this sub-section —`
  line `( a ) “cost of the project” means—`
  line `( i ) in a case referred to in clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ), the actual cost of the fixed assets,`
  line `being land, buildings, leaseholds, plant, machinery, furniture, fittings and railway sidings`
  line `(including expenditure on development of land and buildings), which are shown in the books of`
  line `the assessee as on the last day of the previous year in which the business of the assessee`
  line commences;
  line `( ii ) in a case referred to in clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 1 ), the actual cost of the fixed assets,`
  line `being land, buildings, leaseholds, plant, machinery, furniture, fittings and railway sidings`
  line `(including expenditure on development of land and buildings), which are shown in the books of`
  line `the assessee as on the last day of the previous year in which the extension of the 2 [undertaking] is`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 8, for “industrial undertaking" (w.e.f. 1 -4-2009).`
