obj_root_law_sections_208_content:
  string
  line 208
  line `( ii ) the provisions of this section shall, as far as may be, apply to the resulting company, as they`
  line `would have applied to the demerged company, if the demerger had not taken place.]`
  line `( 6 ) Where a deduction under this section is claimed and allowed for any assessment year in respect of`
  line `any expenditure specified in sub-section ( 2 ), the expenditure in respect of which deduction is so allowed`
  line `shall not qualify for deduction under any other provision of this Act for the same or any other assessment`
  line year.
  line `1 [ 35DD. Amortisation of expenditure in case of amalgamation or demerger. — ( 1 ) Where an`
  line `assessee, being an Indian company, incurs any expenditure, on or after the 1st day of April, 1999, wholly`
  line `and exclusively for the purposes of amalgamation or demerger of an undertaking, the assessee shall be`
  line `allowed a deduction of an amount equal to one-fifth of such expenditure for each of the five successive`
  line `previous years beginning with the previous year in which the amalgamation or demerger takes place.`
  line `( 2 ) No deduction shall be allowed in respect of the expenditure mentioned in sub-section ( 1 ) under`
  line `any other provision of this Act.]`
  line `2 [ 35DDA. Amortisation of expenditure incurred under voluntary retirement scheme. — ( 1 )`
  line `Where an assessee incurs any expenditure in any previous year by way of payment of any sum to an`
  line `employee 3 [in connection with his voluntary retirement], in accordance with any scheme or schemes of`
  line `voluntary retirement, one-fifth of the amount so paid shall be deducted in computing the profits and gains`
  line `of the business for that previous year, and the balance shall be deducted in equal instalments for each of`
  line `the four immediately succeeding previous years.]`
  line `4 [( 2 ) Where the assessee, being an Indian company, is entitled to the deduction under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `and the undertaking of such Indian company entitled to the deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) is transferred,`
  line `before the expiry of the period specified in that sub-section, to another Indian company in a scheme of`
  line `amalgamation, the provisions of this section shall, as far as may be, apply to the amalgamated company`
  line `as they would have applied to the amalgamating company if the amalgamation had not taken place.`
  line `( 3 ) Where the undertaking of an Indian company entitled to the deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) is`
  line `transferred, before the expiry of the period specified in that sub-section, to another company in a scheme`
  line `of demerger, the provisions of this section shall, as far as may be, apply to the resulting company, as they`
  line `would have applied to the demerged company, if the demerger had not taken place.`
  line `( 4 ) Where there has been reorganisation of business, whereby a firm is succeeded by a company`
  line `fulfilling the conditions laid down in clause ( xiii ) of section 47 or a proprietary concern is succeeded by a`
  line `company fulfilling the conditions laid down in clause ( xiv ) of section 47, the provisions of this section`
  line `shall, as far as may be, apply to the successor company, as they would have applied to the firm or the`
  line `proprietary concern, if reorganisation of business had not taken place.`
  line `5 [( 4A ) Where there has been reorganisation ofbusiness, whereby a private company or unlisted public`
  line `company is succeeded by a limited liability partnership fulfilling the conditions laid down in the proviso`
  line `to clause ( xiiib ) of section 47, the provisions of this section shall, as far as may be, apply to the successor`
  line `limited liability partnership, as they would have applied to the said company, if reorganisation of business`
  line `had not taken place.`
  line `( 5 ) No deduction shall be allowed in respect of the expenditure mentioned in sub-section ( 1 ) in the`
  line `case of the amalgamating company referred to in sub-section ( 2 ), in the case of demerged company`
  line `referred to in 6 [sub-section ( 3 ), in the case of a firm or proprietary concern referred to in sub-section ( 4 )`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 11, for “at the time of his voluntary retirement” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2004).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 18, for sub-section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-2011).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for “sub -section ( 3 ) and in the case of a firm or proprietary concern referred to in sub-section ( 4 )”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2011).`
