obj_root_law_sections_209_content:
  string
  line 209
  line `and in the case of a company referred to in sub-section ( 4A )] of this section, for the previous year in`
  line `which amalgamation, demerger or succession, as the case may be, takes place.`
  line `( 6 ) No deduction shall be allowed in respect of the expenditure mentioned in sub-section ( 1 ) under`
  line `any other provision of this Act.]`
  line `35E. Deduction for expenditure on prospecting, etc., for certain minerals. — ( 1 ) Where an`
  line `assessee, being an Indian company or a person (other than a company) who is resident in India, is`
  line `engaged in any operations relating to prospecting for, or extraction or production of, any mineral and`
  line `incurs, after the 31st day of March, 1970, any expenditure specified in sub-section ( 2 ), the assessee shall,`
  line `in accordance with and subject to the provisions of this section, be allowed for each one of the relevant`
  line `previous years a deduction of an amount equal to one-tenth of the amount of such expenditure.`
  line `( 2 ) The expenditure referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) is that incurred by the assessee after the date`
  line `specified in that sub-section at any time during the year of commercial production and any one or more of`
  line `the four years immediately preceding that year, wholly and exclusively on any operations relating to`
  line `prospecting for any mineral or group of associated minerals specified in Part A or Part B, respectively, of`
  line `the Seventh Schedule or on the development of a mine or other natural deposit of any such mineral or`
  line `group of associated minerals:`
  line `Provided that there shall be excluded from such expenditure any portion thereof which is met directly`
  line `or indirectly by any other person or authority and any sale, salvage, compensation or insurance moneys`
  line `realised by the assessee in respect of any property or rights brought into existence as a result of the`
  line expenditure.
  line `( 3 ) Any expenditure —`
  line `( i ) on the acquisition of the site of the source of any mineral or group of associated minerals`
  line `referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) or of any rights in or over such site;`
  line `( ii ) on the acquisition of the deposits of such mineral or group of associated minerals or of any`
  line `rights in or over such deposits; or`
  line `( iii ) of a capital nature in respect of any building, machinery, plant or furniture for which`
  line `allowance by way of depreciation is admissible under section 32,`
  line `shall not be deemed to be expenditure incurred by the assessee for any of the purposes specified in`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ).`
  line `( 4 ) The deduction to be allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) for any relevant previous year shall be —`
  line `( a ) an amount equal to one-tenth of the expenditure specified in sub-section ( 2 ) (such one-tenth`
  line `being hereafter in this sub-section referred to as the instalment); or`
  line `( b ) such amount as is sufficient to reduce to nil the income (as computed before making the`
  line `deduction under this section) of that previous year arising from the commercial exploitation [whether`
  line `or not such commercial exploitation is as a result of the operations or development referred to in sub-`
  line `section ( 2 )] of any mine or other natural deposit of the mineral or any one or more of the minerals in a`
  line `group of associated minerals as aforesaid in respect of which the expenditure was incurred,`
