obj_root_law_sections_210_content:
  string
  line 210
  line `whichever amount is less:`
  line `Provided that the amount of the instalment relating to any relevant previous year, to the extent to`
  line `which it remains unallowed, shall be carried forward and added to the instalment relating to the previous`
  line `year next following and deemed to be part of that instalment, and so on, for succeeding previous years,`
  line `so, however, that no part of any instalment shall be carried forward beyond the tenth previous year as`
  line `reckoned from the year of commercial production.`
  line `( 5 ) For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “operation relating to prospecting” means any operation undertaken for the purposes of`
  line `exploring, locating or proving deposits of any mineral, and includes any such operation which proves`
  line `to be infructuous or abortive;`
  line `( b ) “year of commercial production” means the previous year in which as a result of any`
  line `operation relating to prospecting, commercial production of any mineral or any one or more of the`
  line `minerals in a group of associated minerals specified in Part A or Part B, respectively, of the Seventh`
  line `Schedule, commences;`
  line `( c ) “relevant previous years” means the ten previous years beginning with the year of commercial`
  line production.
  line `( 6 ) Where the assessee is a person other than a company or a co-operative society, no deduction shall`
  line `be admissible under sub-section ( 1 ) unless the accounts of the assessee for the year or years in which the`
  line `expenditure specified in sub-section ( 2 ) is incurred have been audited by an accountant as defined in`
  line `the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288, and the assessee furnishes, along with his return of`
  line `income for the first year in which the deduction under this section is claimed, the report of such audit in`
  line `the prescribed form duly signed and verified by such accountant and setting forth such particulars as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line `( 7 ) Where the undertaking of an Indian company which is entitled to the deduction under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) is transferred, before the expiry of the period of ten years specified in sub-section ( 1 ), to`
  line `another Indian company in a scheme of amalgamation —`
  line `( i ) no deduction shall be admissible under sub-section ( 1 ) in the case of the amalgamating`
  line `company for the previous year in which the amalgamation takes place; and`
  line `( ii ) the provisions of this section shall, as far as may be, apply to the amalgamated company as`
  line `they would have applied to the amalgamating company if the amalgamation had not taken place.`
  line `1 [( 7A ) Where the undertaking of an Indian company which is entitled to the deduction under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) is transferred, before the expiry of the period of ten years specified in sub-section ( 1 ), to`
  line `another Indian company in a scheme of demerger, —`
  line `( i ) no deduction shall be admissible under sub-section ( 1 ) in the case of the demerged company`
  line `for the previous year in which the demerger takes place; and`
  line `( ii ) the provisions of this section shall, as far as may be, apply to the resulting company as they`
  line `would have applied to the demerged company, if the demerger had not taken place.]`
  line `( 8 ) Where a deduction under this section is claimed and allowed for any assessment year in respect of`
  line `any expenditure specified in sub-section ( 2 ), the expenditure in respect of which deduction is so allowed`
  line `shall not qualify for deduction under any other provision of this Act for the same or any other assessment`
  line year.]
  line `1. Ins. by 27 of 1999, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
