obj_root_law_sections_211_content:
  string
  line 211
  line `36. Other deductions. — ( 1 ) The deductions provided for in the following clauses shall be allowed in`
  line `respect of the matters dealt with therein, in computing the income referred to in section 28 —`
  line `( i ) the amount of any premium paid in respect of insurance against risk of damage or destruction`
  line `of stocks or stores used for the purposes of the business or profession;`
  line `1 [( ia ) the amount of any premium paid by a federal milk co-operative society to effect or to keep`
  line `in force an insurance on the life of the cattle owned by a member of a co-operative society, being a`
  line `primary society engaged in supplying milk raised by its members to such federal milk co-operative`
  line society;]
  line `2 [( ib ) the amount of any premium paid by any mode of payment other than cash by the assessee`
  line `as an employer to effect or to keep in force an insurance on the health of his employees under a`
  line `scheme framed in this behalf by —`
  line `( A ) the General Insurance Corporation of India formed under section 9 of the General`
  line `Insurance Business (Nationalisation) Act, 1972 (57 of 1972) and approved by the Central`
  line `Government; or`
  line `( B ) any other insurer and approved by the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority`
  line `established under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 3 of the Insurance Regulatory and Development`
  line `Authority Act, 1999 (41 of 1999);]`
  line `( ii ) any sum paid to an employee as bonus or commission for services rendered, where such sum`
  line `would not have been payable to him as profits or dividend if it had not been paid as bonus or`
  line commission;
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `( iii ) the amount of the interest paid in respect of capital borrowed for the purposes of the business`
  line `or profession:`
  line `5 [Provided that any amount of the interest paid, in respect of capital borrowed for acquisition of`
  line `an asset 6 *** (whether capitalised in the books of account or not); for any period beginning from the`
  line `date on which the capital was borrowed for acquisition of the asset till the date on which such asset`
  line `was first put to use, shall not be allowed as deduction.`
  line `Explanation. — Recurring subscriptions paid periodically by shareholders, or subscribers in`
  line `Mutual Benefit Societies which fulfill such conditions as may be prescribed, shall be deemed to be`
  line `capital borrowed within the meaning of this clause;`
  line `7 [( iiia ) the pro rata amount of discount on a zero coupon bond having regard to the period of life`
  line `of such bond calculated in the manner as may be prescribed.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1979, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-1980).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 9, for clause ( ib ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `3. The provisos omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. Clause ( iia ) omitted by Act 27 of 1999, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `6. The wor ds “for extension of existing business or profession” omitted by Act 20 of 2015, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1 -4-2016).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
