obj_root_law_sections_212_content:
  string
  line 212
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, the expressions —`
  line `( i ) “discount” means the difference between the amount received or receivable by the`
  line `infrastructure capital company or infrastructure capital fund or public sector company 1 [or`
  line `scheduled bank] issuing the bond and the amount payable by such company or fund or public`
  line `sector company 1 [or scheduled bank] on maturity or redemption of such bond;`
  line `( ii ) “period of life of the bond” means the period commencing from the date of issue of the`
  line `bond and ending on the date of the maturity or redemption of such bond;`
  line `2 * * * * *]`
  line `( iv ) any sum paid by the assessee as an employer by way of contribution towards a recognised`
  line `provident fund or an approved superannuation fund, subject to such limits as may be prescribed for`
  line `the purpose of recognising the provident fund or approving the superannuation fund, as the case may`
  line `be; and subject to such conditions as the Board may think fit to specify in cases where the`
  line `contributions are not in the nature of annual contributions of fixed amounts or annual contributions`
  line `fixed on some definite basis by reference to the income chargeable under the head “Salaries” or to the`
  line `contributions or to the number of members of the fund;`
  line `3 [( iva ) any sum paid by the assessee as an employer by way of contribution towards a pension`
  line `scheme, as referred to in section 80CCD, on account of an employee to the extent it does not exceed`
  line `ten per cent of the salary of the employee in the previous year.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purp oses of this clause, “salary” includes dearness allowance, if the terms`
  line `of employment so provide, but excludes all other allowances and perquisites;]`
  line `( v ) any sum paid by the assessee as an employer by way of contribution towards an approved`
  line `gratuity fund created by him for the exclusive benefit of his employees under an irrevocable trust;`
  line `4 [( va ) any sum received by the assessee from any of his employees to which the provisions of`
  line `sub-clause ( x ) of clause ( 24 ) of section 2 apply, if such sum is credited by the assessee to the`
  line `employee’s account in the relevant fund or funds on or before the due date.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, “due date” means the date by which the assessee is`
  line `required as an employer to credit an employee's contribution to the employee's account in the relevant`
  line `fund under any Act, rule, order or notification issued thereunder or under any standing order, award,`
  line `contract of service or otherwise;]`
  line `( vi ) in respect of animals which have been used for the purposes of the business or profession`
  line `otherwise than as stock-in-trade and have died or become permanently useless for such purposes, the`
  line `difference between the actual cost to the assessee of the animals and the amount, if any, realised in`
  line `respect of the carcasses or animals;`
  line `( vii ) subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ), the amount of 5 [any bad debt or part thereof`
  line `which is written off as irrecoverable in the accounts of the assessee for the previous year:]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
  line `2. Clause ( iii ) omitted by Act 21 of 2006, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2012).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 11, for “any debt, or part thereof, which is established to have become a bad debt in the`
  line `previous year” (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
