obj_root_law_sections_214_content:
  string
  line 214
  line `1 [Provided further that for the relevant assessment years commencing on or after the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2003 and ending before the 1st day of April, 2005, the provisions of the first proviso shall have`
  line `effect as if for the words “five per cent”, the words “ten per cent.” had been substituted:]`
  line `2 [Provided also that a scheduled bank or a non-scheduled bank referred to in this sub-clause shall,`
  line `at its option, be allowed a further deduction in excess of the limits specified in the foregoing`
  line `provisions, for an amount not exceeding the income derived from redemption of securities in`
  line `accordance with a scheme framed by the Central Government:`
  line `Provided also that no deduction shall be allowed under the third proviso unless such income has`
  line `been disclosed in the return of income under the head “Profits and gains of business or prof ession.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- clause, “relevant assessment years” means the five`
  line `consecutive assessment years commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 2000 and ending before`
  line `the 1st day of April, 2005;]`
  line `( b ) a bank, being a bank incorporated by or under the laws of a country outside India, an amount`
  line `not exceeding five per cent of the total income (computed before making any deduction under this`
  line `clause and Chapter VI-A);]`
  line `3 [( c ) a public financial institution or a State financial corporation or a State industrial investment`
  line `corporation, an amount not exceeding five per cent of the total income (computed before making any`
  line `deduction under this clause and Chapter VI-A):]`
  line `1 [Provided that a public financial institution or a State financial corporation or a State industrial`
  line `investment corporation referred to in this sub-clause shall, at its option, be allowed in any of the two`
  line `consecutive assessment years commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 2003 and ending before`
  line `the 1st day of April, 2005, deduction in respect of any provision made by it for any assets classified`
  line `by the Reserve Bank of India as doubtful assets or loss assets in accordance with the guidelines issued`
  line `by it in this behalf, of an amount not exceeding ten per cent of the amount of such assets shown in the`
  line `books of account of such institution or corporation, as the case may be, on the last day of the previous`
  line year.]
  line `4 [( d ) a non-banking financial company, an amount not exceeding five per cent. of the total`
  line `income (computed before making any deduction under this clause and Chapter VI-A).]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `5 [( i ) “non - scheduled bank” means a banking company as defined in clause ( c ) of section 5 of`
  line `the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), which is not a scheduled bank;`
  line `6 [( ia )]“rural branch” means a branch of a scheduled bank 7 [or a non-scheduled bank] situated`
  line `in a place which has a population of not more than ten thousand according to the last preceding`
  line `census of which the relevant figures have been published before the first day of the previous year;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 19 (w.e.f 1-4-2003).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 14 of 1982, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-983).`
  line `6. Clause ( i ) renumbered as clause ( ia ) thereof by Act 14 of 1982, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-1983).`
  line `7. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1983).`
