obj_root_law_sections_217_content:
  string
  line 217
  line `( iii ) an undertaking referred to in sub-section ( 10 ) of section 80-IB;`
  line `( h ) “long - term finance” means any loan or advance where the terms under which moneys`
  line `are loaned or advanced provide for repayment along with interest thereof during a period of`
  line `not less than five years;]`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `2 [( ix ) any expenditure bona fide incurred by a company for the purpose of promoting family`
  line `planning amongst its employees:`
  line `Provided that where such expenditure or any part thereof is of a capital nature, one-fifth of`
  line `such expenditure shall be deducted for the previous year in which it was incurred; and the balance`
  line `thereof shall be deducted in equal instalments for each of the four immediately succeeding`
  line `previous years:`
  line `Provided further that the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 32 and of sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 72 shall apply in relation to deductions allowable under this clause as they apply in`
  line `relation to deductions allowable in respect of depreciation:`
  line `Provided further that the provisions of clauses ( ii ), ( iii ), ( iv ) and ( v ) of 3 [sub-section ( 2 ) and`
  line `sub-section ( 5 ) of section 35], of sub-section ( 3 ) of section 41 and of Explanation 1 to clause ( 1 )`
  line `of section 43 shall, so far as may be, apply in relation to an asset representing expenditure of a`
  line `capital nature for the purposes of promoting family planning as they apply in relation to an asset`
  line `representing expenditure of a capital nature on scientific research;]`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `5 [( xi ) any expenditure incurred by the assessee, on or after the 1st day of April, 1999 but`
  line `before the 1st day of April, 2000, wholly and exclusively in respect of a non-Y2K compliant`
  line `computer system, owned by the assessee and used for the purposes of his business or profession,`
  line `so as to make such computer system Y2K compliant computer system:`
  line `Provided that no such deduction shall be allowed in respect of such expenditure under any`
  line `other provisions of this Act:`
  line `Provided further that no such deduction shall be admissible unless the assessee furnishes in`
  line `the prescribed form, along with the return of income, the report of an accountant, as defined in`
  line `the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288, certifying that the deduction has been`
  line `correctly claimed in accordance with the provisions of this clause.`
  line `1. Clause ( viiia ) omitted by Act 32 of 1994, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 15, for “sub -section ( 2 ) of section 35” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1967).`
  line `4. Clause ( x ) omitted by Act 22 of 2007, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_217_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_218:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-218
  sectionNo (218)
  orderNo 218
  title `Page 218`
  content obj_root_law_sections_218_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_218_footnotes
  sourcePage 218
obj_root_law_sections_218_content:
  string
  line 218
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( a ) “computer system” means a device or collection of devices including input and`
  line `output support devices and excluding calculators which are not programmable and capable of`
  line `being used in conjunction with external files, or more of which contain computer`
  line `programmes, electronic instructions, input data and output data, that performs functions`
  line `including, but not limited to, logic, arithmetic, data storage and retrieval, communication and`
  line control;
  line `( b ) “Y2K compliant computer system” means a computer system capable of correctly`
  line `processing, providing or receiving data relating to date within and between the twentieth and`
  line `twenty-first century;]`
  line `1 [( xii ) any expenditure (not being in the nature of capital expenditure) incurred by a`
  line `corporation or a body corporate, by whatever name called, if, —`
  line `( a ) it is constituted or established by gjma Central, State or Provincial Act;`
  line `( b ) such corporation or body corporate, having regard to the objects and purposes of the`
  line `Act referred to in sub-clause ( a ), is notified by the Central Government in the Official`
  line `Gazette for the purposes of this clause; and`
  line `( c ) the expenditure is incurred for the objects and purposes authorised by the Act under`
  line `which it is constituted or established;]`
  line `2 [( xiii ) any amount of banking cash transaction tax paid by the assessee during the previous`
  line `year on the taxable banking transactions entered into by him.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, the expressions “banking cash transaction tax”`
  line `and “taxable banking transaction” shall have the same meanings respectively assigned to them`
  line `under Chapter VII of the Finance Act, 2005;]`
  line `3 [( xiv ) any sum paid by a public financial institution by way of contribution to such credit`
  line `guarantee fund trust for small industries as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, specify in this behalf.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, “public financial institution” shall have the`
  line `meaning assigned to it in section 4A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);]`
  line `4 [( xv ) an amount equal to the securities transaction tax paid by the assessee in respect of the`
  line `taxable securities transactions entered into in the course of his business during the previous year,`
  line `if the income arising from such taxable securities transactions is included in the income computed`
  line `under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession”.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 13, for clause ( xii ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_218_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_219:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-219
  sectionNo (219)
  orderNo 219
  title `Page 219`
  content obj_root_law_sections_219_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_219_footnotes
  sourcePage 219
obj_root_law_sections_219_content:
  string
  line 219
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, the expressions “securities transaction tax”`
  line `and “taxable securities transaction” shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them under`
  line `Chapter VII of the Finance (No. 2) Act, 2004 (23 of 2004);`
  line `1 [( xvi ) an amount equal to the commodities transaction tax paid by the assessee in respect of`
  line `the taxable commodities transactions entered into in the course of his business during the`
  line `previous year, if the income arising from such taxable commodities transactions is included in the`
  line `income computed under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession”.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, the expressions “commodities transaction tax”`
  line `and “taxable commodities transaction” shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them`
  line `under Chapter VII of the Finance Act, 2013;]]`
  line `2 [( xvii ) the amount of expenditure incurred by a co-operative society engaged in the business`
  line `of manufacture of sugar for purchase of sugarcane at a price which is equal to or less than the`
  line `price fixed or approved by the Government.]`
  line `3 [( xviii ) marked to market loss or other expected loss as computed in accordance with the`
  line `income computation and disclosure standards notified under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 145.]`
  line `( 2 ) In making any deduction for a bad debt or part thereof, the following provisions shall apply —`
  line `4 [( i ) no such deduction shall be allowed unless such debt or part thereof has been taken into`
  line `account in computing the income of the assessee of the previous year in which the amount of such`
  line `debt or part thereof is written off or of an earlier previous year, or represents money lent in the`
  line `ordinary course of the business of banking or money-lending which is carried on by the assessee;]`
  line `( ii ) if the amount ultimately recovered on any such debt or part of debt is less than the difference`
  line `between the debt or part and the amount so deducted, the deficiency shall be deductible in the`
  line `previous year in which the ultimate recovery is made;`
  line `( iii ) any such debt or part of debt may be deducted if it has already been written off as`
  line `irrecoverable in the accounts of an earlier previous year 5 [(being a previous year relevant to the`
  line `assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1988, or any earlier assessment year)], but the`
  line `6 [Assessing Officer] had not allowed it to be deducted on the ground that it had not been established`
  line `to have become a bad debt in that year;`
  line `( iv ) where any such debt or part of debt is written off as irrecoverable in the accounts of the`
  line `previous year 5 [(being a previous year relevant to the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 1988, or any earlier assessment year)] and the 6 [Assessing Officer] is satisfied that such debt or`
  line `part became a bad debt in any earlier previous year not falling beyond a period of four previous years`
  line `immediately preceding the previous year in which such debt or part is written off, the provisions of`
  line `sub-section ( 6 ) of section 155 shall apply;`
  line `7 [( v ) where such debt or part of debt relates to advances made by an assessee to which`
  line `clause ( viia ) of sub-section ( 1 ) applies, no such deduction shall be allowed unless the assessee has`
  line `debited the amount of such debt or part of debt in that previous year to the provision for bad and`
  line `doubtful debts account made under that clause.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 10 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 11, for clause ( i ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 7, for clause ( v ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
obj_root_law_sections_219_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_220:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-220
  sectionNo (220)
  orderNo 220
  title `Page 220`
  content obj_root_law_sections_220_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_220_footnotes
  sourcePage 220
obj_root_law_sections_220_content:
  string
  line 220
  line `37. General. — ( 1 ) Any expenditure (not being expenditure of the nature described in`
  line `sections 30 to 36 1 *** and not being in the nature of capital expenditure or personal expenses of the`
  line `assessee), laid out or expended wholly and exclusively for the purposes of the business or profession shall`
  line `be a llowed in computing the income chargeable under the head “Profits and gains of business or`
  line profession”.
  line `2 [ 3 [ Explanation 1.] — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that any expenditure incurred`
  line `by an assessee for any purpose which is an offence or which is prohibited by law shall not be deemed to`
  line `have been incurred for the purpose of business or profession and no deduction or allowance shall be made`
  line `in respect of such expenditure.]`
  line `4 [ Explanation 2. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that for the purposes of sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ), any expenditure incurred by an assessee on the activities relating to corporate social`
  line `responsibility referred to in section 135 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013) shall not be deemed to`
  line `be an expenditure incurred by the assessee for the purposes of the business or profession.]`
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `6 [( 2B ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), no allowance shall be made in respect`
  line `of expenditure incurred by an assessee on advertisement in any souvenir, brochure, tract, pamphlet or the`
  line `like published by a political party.]`
  line `7 * * * * *`
  line `8 * * * * *`
  line `9 * * * * *`
  line `38. Building, etc., partly used for business, etc., or not exclusively so used. — ( 1 ) Where a part of`
  line `any premises is used as dwelling house by the assessee, —`
  line `( a ) the deduction under sub-clause ( i ) of clause ( a ) of section 30, in the case of rent, shall be such`
  line `amount as the 10 [Assessing Officer] may determine having regard to the proportionate annual value of`
  line `the part used for the purpose of the business or profession, and in the case of any sum paid for repairs,`
  line `such sum as is proportionate to the part of the premises used for the purpose of the business or`
  line profession;
  line `( b ) the deduction under clause ( b ) of section 30 shall be such sum as the 8 [Assessing Officer] may`
  line `determine having regard to the part so used.`
  line `( 2 ) Where any building, machinery, plant or furniture is not exclusively used for the purposes of the`
  line `business or profession, the deductions under sub-clause ( ii ) of clause ( a ) and clause ( c ) of section 30,`
  line `1. The words “and section 80VV” omitted by Act 32 of 1985, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1986).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `3. Explanation numbered as Explanation 1 thereof by Act 25 of 2014, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `5. Sub-section ( 2 ) omitted by Act 26 of 1997, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 29 of 1978, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1979).`
  line `7. Sub-section ( 3 ) omitted by Act 26 of 1997, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `8. Sub-sections ( 3A ), ( 3B ), ( 3C ) and ( 3D ) omitted by Act 32 of 1985, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1986).`
  line `9. Sub-sections ( 4 ) and ( 5 ) omitted by Act 26 of 1997, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer”, (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
