obj_root_law_sections_221_content:
  string
  line 221
  line `clauses ( i ) and ( ii ) of section 31 and 1 [clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 1 )] of section 32 shall be restricted to a`
  line `fair proportionate part thereof which the 2 [Assessing Officer] may determine, having regard to the user of`
  line `such building, machinery, plant or furniture for the purposes of the business or profession.`
  line `39. Managing agency commission. — Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws ( Amendment )`
  line `Act, 1987 (4 of 1988), s. 12, ( w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `40. Amounts not deductible. — Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in 3 [section 30 to 38], the`
  line `following amounts shall not be deducted in computing the income chargeable under the head “Profits and`
  line `gains of business or p rofession”,—`
  line `( a ) in the case of any assessee —`
  line `4 [( i ) any interest (not being interest on a loan issued for public subscription before the 1st day`
  line `of April, 1938), royalty, fees for technical services or other sum chargeable under this Act, which`
  line `is payable, —`
  line `( A ) outside India; or`
  line `( B ) in India to a non-resident, not being a company or to a foreign company,`
  line `on which tax is deductible at source under Chapter XVII-B and such tax has not been deducted`
  line `or, after deduction, has not been paid 5 [on or before the due date specified in sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 139]:`
  line `6 [Provided that where in respect of any such sum, tax has been deducted in any subsequent`
  line `year, or has been deducted during the previous year but paid after the due date specified in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139, such sum shall be allowed as a deduction in computing the income`
  line `of the previous year in which such tax has been paid.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-clause, —`
  line `( A ) “royalty” shall have the same meaning as in Explanation 2 to clause ( vi ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 9;`
  line `( B ) “fees for technical services” shall have the same meaning as in Explanation 2 to`
  line `clause ( vii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 9;`
  line `( ia ) 7 [thirty per cent of any sum payable to a resident], on which tax is deductible at source`
  line `under Chapter XVII-B and such tax has not been deducted or, after deduction, 8 [has not been paid`
  line `on or before the due date specified in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139:]`
  line `9 [Provided that where in respect of any such sum, tax has been deducted in any subsequent`
  line `year, or has been deducted during the previous year but paid after the due date specified in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139, 10 [thirty per cent of] such sum shall be allowed as a deduction in`
  line `computing the income of the previous year in which such tax has been paid:]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 32, for “clause ( i ), ( ii ), ( iia ) and ( iii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) and sub-section ( 1A )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-`
  line `1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for “section 30 to 39” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 11, for sub-clause ( i ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 14, for certain words, brackets and figures (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for certain words and brackets (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 12, for certain words, brackets and figures (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `9. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for proviso (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
