obj_root_law_sections_222_content:
  string
  line 222
  line `1 [Provided further that where an assessee fails to deduct the whole or any part of the tax in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of Chapter XVII-B on any such sum but is not deemed to be an`
  line `assessee in default under the first proviso to sub-section ( 1 ) of section 201, then, for the purpose`
  line `of this sub-clause, it shall be deemed that the assessee has deducted and paid the tax on such sum`
  line `on the date of furnishing of return of income by the resident payee referred to in the said proviso.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-clause, —`
  line `( i ) “commission or brokerage” shall have the same meaning as in clause ( i ) of`
  line `the Explanation to section 194H;`
  line `( ii ) “fees for technical services” shall have the sam e meaning as in Explanation 2 to`
  line `clause ( vii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 9;`
  line `( iii ) “professional services” shall have the same meaning as in clause ( a ) of`
  line `the Explanation to section 194J;`
  line `( iv ) “work” shall have the same meaning as in Explanation III to section 194C;`
  line `2 [( v ) “rent” shall have the same meaning as in clause ( i ) to the Explanation to`
  line `section 194-I;`
  line `( vi ) “royalty” shall have the same meaning as in Explanation 2 to clause ( vi ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 9;]`
  line `3 [( ib ) any consideration paid or payable to a non-resident for a specified service on which`
  line `equalisation levy is deductible under the provisions of Chapter VIII of the Finance Act, 2016, and`
  line `such levy has not been deducted or after deduction, has not been paid on or before the due date`
  line `specified in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139:`
  line `Provided that where in respect of any such consideration, the equalisation levy has been`
  line `deducted in any subsequent year or has been deducted during the previous year but paid after the`
  line `due date specified in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139, such sum shall be allowed as a deduction in`
  line `computing the income of the previous year in which such levy has been paid;]]`
  line `4 [( ic ) any sum paid on account of fringe benefit tax under Chapter XIIH;]`
  line `( ii ) any sum paid on account of any rate or tax levied on the profits or gains of any business`
  line `or profession or assessed at a proportion of, or otherwise on the basis of, any such profits or`
  line gains.
  line `5 [ Explanation 1. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that for the purposes of`
  line `this sub-clause, any sum paid on account of any rate or tax levied includes and shall be deemed`
  line `always to have included any sum eligible for relief of tax under section 90 or, as the case may be,`
  line `deduction from the Indian income-tax payable under section 91.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
