obj_root_law_sections_223_content:
  string
  line 223
  line `1 [ Explanation 2. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that for the purposes of`
  line `this sub-clause, any sum paid on account of any rate or tax levied includes any sum eligible for`
  line `relief of tax under section 90A;]`
  line `2 [( iia ) any sum paid on account of wealth-tax.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- clause, “wealth - tax” means wealth -tax chargeable`
  line `under the Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957), or any tax of a similar character chargeable under`
  line `any law in force in any country outside India or any tax chargeable under such law with reference`
  line `to the value of the assets of, or the capital employed in, a business or profession carried on by the`
  line `assessee, whether or not the debts of the business or profession are allowed as a deduction in`
  line `computing the amount with reference to which such tax is charged, but does not include any tax`
  line `chargeable with reference to the value of any particular asset of the business or profession;]`
  line `3 [( iib ) any amount —`
  line `( A ) paid by way of royalty, licence fee, service fee, privilege fee, service charge or any`
  line `other fee or charge, by whatever name called, which is levied exclusively on; or`
  line `( B ) which is appropriated, directly or indirectly, from, a State Government undertaking`
  line `by the State Government.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-clause, a State Government undertaking`
  line `includes —`
  line `( i ) a corporation established by or under any Act of the State Government;`
  line `( ii ) a company in which more than fifty per cent of the paid-up equity share capital is`
  line `held by the State Government;`
  line `( iii ) a company in which more than fifty per cent of the paid-up equity share capital is`
  line `held by the entity referred to in clause ( i ) or clause ( ii ) (whether singly or taken together);`
  line `( iv ) a company or corporation in which the State Government has the right to appoint the`
  line `majority of the directors or to control the management or policy decisions, directly or`
  line `indirectly, including by virtue of its shareholding or management rights or shareholders`
  line `agreements or voting agreements or in any other manner;`
  line `( v ) an authority, a board or an institution or a body established or constituted by or under`
  line `any Act of the State Government or owned or controlled by the State Government;]`
  line `4 [( iii ) any payment which is chargeable under the head “Salaries”, if it is payable—`
  line `( A ) outside India; or`
  line `( B ) to a non-resident,`
  line `and if the tax has not been paid thereon nor deducted therefrom under Chapter XVII-B;]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-6-2006).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 41 of 1972, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 19, for sub-clause ( iii ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
