obj_root_law_sections_224_content:
  string
  line 224
  line `( iv ) any payment to a provident or other fund established for the benefit of employees of the`
  line `assessee, unless the assessee has made effective arrangements to secure that tax shall be deducted`
  line `at source from any payments made from the fund which are chargeable to tax under the head`
  line “Salaries”;
  line `1 [( v ) any tax actually paid by an employer referred to in clause ( 10CC ) of section 10;]`
  line `2 [( b ) in the case of any firm assessable as such, —`
  line `( i ) any payment of salary, bonus, commission or remuneration, by whatever name called`
  line `(herein after referred to as “remuneration”) to any partner who is not a working partner; or`
  line `( ii ) any payment of remuneration to any partner who is a working partner, or of interest to`
  line `any partner, which, in either case, is not authorised by, or is not in accordance with, the terms of`
  line `the partnership deed; or`
  line `( iii ) any payment of remuneration to any partner who is a working partner, or of interest to`
  line `any partner, which, in either case, is authorised by, and is in accordance with, the terms of the`
  line `partnership deed, but which relates to any period (falling prior to the date of such partnership`
  line `deed) for which such payment was not authorised by, or is not in accordance with, any earlier`
  line `partnership deed, so, however, that the period of authorisation for such payment by any earlier`
  line `partnership deed does not cover any period prior to the date of such earlier partnership deed; or`
  line `( iv ) any payment of interest to any partner which is authorised by, and is in accordance with,`
  line `the terms of the partnership deed and relates to any period falling after the date of such`
  line `partnership deed in so far as such amount exceeds the amount calculated at the rate of 3 [twelve`
  line `per cent.] simple interest per annum; or`
  line `( v ) any payment of remuneration to any partner who is a working partner, which is authorised`
  line `by, and is in accordance with, the terms of the partnership deed and relates to any period falling`
  line `after the date of such partnership deed in so far as the amount of such payment to all the partners`
  line `during the previous year exceeds the aggregate amount computed as hereunder: —`
  line `4 [( a ) on the first Rs. 3,00,000 of the Rs. 1,50,000 or at the rate of 90 per cent.`
  line `book-profit or in case of a loss of the book-profit, whichever is more;`
  line `( b ) on the balance of the book-profit at the rate of 60 per cent:]`
  line `Provided that in relation to any payment under this clause to the partner during the previous`
  line `year relevant to the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1993, the terms of the`
  line `partnership deed may, at any time during the said previous year, provide for such payment.`
  line `Explanation 1. — Where an individual is a partner in a firm on behalf, or for the benefit, of`
  line `any other person (such p artner and the other person being hereinafter referred to as “partner in a`
  line `representative capacity” and “person so represented”, respectively),—`
  line `( i ) interest paid by the firm to such individual otherwise than as partner in a`
  line `representative capacity, shall not be taken into account for the purposes of this clause;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 16, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1993). Earlier amended by Act 67 of 1984, s. 10`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1985), Act 4 of 1988, s. 13 and 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 20, for “eighteen per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2002).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 15, for Items ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
