  content obj_root_law_sections_225_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_225_footnotes
  sourcePage 225
obj_root_law_sections_225_content:
  string
  line 225
  line `( ii ) interest paid by the firm to such individual as partner in a representative capacity and`
  line `interest paid by the firm to the person so represented shall be taken into account for the`
  line `purposes of this clause.`
  line `Explanation 2. — Where an individual is a partner in a firm otherwise than as partner in a`
  line `representative capacity, interest paid by the firm to such individual shall not be taken into account`
  line `for the purposes of this clause, if such interest is received by him on behalf, or for the benefit, of`
  line `any other person.`
  line `Explanation 3. —For the purposes of this clause, “book - profit” means the net profit, as shown`
  line `in the profit and loss account for the relevant previous year, computed in the manner laid down in`
  line `Chapter IV-D as increased by the aggregate amount of the remuneration paid or payable to all the`
  line `partners of the firm if such amount has been deducted while computing the net profit.`
  line `Explanation 4. —For the purposes of this clause, “working partner” means an individual who`
  line `is actively engaged in conducting the affairs of the business or profession of the firm of which he`
  line `is a partner;]`
  line `1 [( ba ) in the case of an association of persons or body of individuals [other than a company or a`
  line `co-operative society or a society registered under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860),`
  line `or under any law corresponding to that Act in force in any part of India], any payment of interest,`
  line `salary, bonus, commission or remuneration, by whatever name called, made by such association or`
  line `body to a member of such association or body.`
  line `Explanation 1. — Where interest is paid by an association or body to any member thereof who has`
  line `also paid interest to the association or body, the amount of interest to be disallowed under this clause`
  line `shall be limited to the amount by which the payment of interest by the association or body to the`
  line `member exceeds the payment of interest by the member to the association or body.`
  line `Explanation 2. — Where an individual is a member of an association or body on behalf, or for the`
  line `benefit, of any other person (such member and the other person being hereinafter referred to as`
  line `“member in a representative capacity” and “person so represented”, respectively),—`
  line `( i ) interest paid by the association or body to such individual or by such individual to the`
  line `association or body otherwise than as member in a representative capacity, shall not be taken into`
  line `account for the purposes of this clause;`
  line `( ii ) interest paid by the association or body to such individual or by such individual to the`
  line `association or body as member in a representative capacity and interest paid by the association or`
  line `body to the person so represented or by the person so represented to the association or body, shall`
  line `be taken into account for the purposes of this clause.`
  line `Explanation 3. — Where an individual is a member of an association or body otherwise than as`
  line `member in a representative capacity, interest paid by the association or body to such individual shall`
  line `not be taken into account for the purposes of this clause, if such interest is received by him on behalf,`
  line `or for the benefit, of any other person.]`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Clause ( c ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Clause ( d ) omitted by Act 26 of 1988, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
