obj_root_law_sections_226_content:
  string
  line 226
  line `1 [40A. Expenses or payments not deductible in certain circumstances. — ( 1 ) The provisions of this`
  line `section shall have effect notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any other provision of this`
  line `Act relating to the computation of income under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession”.`
  line `( 2 ) ( a ) Where the assessee incurs any expenditure in respect of which payment has been or is to be`
  line `made to any person referred to in clause ( b ) of this sub-section, and the 2 [Assessing Officer] is of opinion`
  line `that such expenditure is excessive or unreasonable having regard to the fair market value of the goods,`
  line `services or facilities for which the payment is made or the legitimate needs of the business or profession`
  line `of the assessee or the benefit derived by or accruing to him therefrom, so much of the expenditure as is so`
  line `considered by him to be excessive or unreasonable shall not be allowed as a deduction:`
  line `3 [Provided that 4 [for an assessment year commencing on or before the 1st day of April, 2016] no`
  line `disallowance, on account of any expenditure being excessive or unreasonable having regard to the fair`
  line `market value, shall be made in respect of a specified domestic transaction referred to in section 92BA, if`
  line `such transaction is at arm's length price as defined in clause ( ii ) of section 92F.]`
  line `( b ) The persons referred to in clause ( a ) are the following, namely: —`
  line `( i ) where the assessee is an individual any relative of the assessee;`
  line `( ii ) where the assessee is a company, any director of the company, partner of the firm,`
  line `firm, association of persons or or member of the association or family, or any`
  line `Hindu un-divided family relative of such director, partner or member;`
  line `( iii ) any individual who has a substantial interest in the business or profession of the assessee, or`
  line `any relative of such individual;`
  line `( iv ) a company, firm, association of persons or Hindu undivided family having a substantial`
  line `interest in the business or profession of the assessee or any director, partner or member of such`
  line `company, firm, association or family, or any relative of such director, partner or member 5 [or any`
  line `other company carrying on business or profession in which the first mentioned company has`
  line `substantial interest;]`
  line `( v ) a company, firm, association of persons or Hindu undivided family of which a director,`
  line `partner or member, as the case may be, has a substantial interest in the business or profession of the`
  line `assessee; or any director, partner or member of such company, firm, association or family or any`
  line `relative of such director, partner or member;`
  line `( vi ) any person who carries on a business or profession, —`
  line `( A ) where the assessee being an individual, or any relative of such assessee, has a substantial`
  line `interest in the business or profession of that person; or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 19 of 1968, s. 7 (w.e.f 1-4-1968).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_226_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_227:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-227
  sectionNo (227)
  orderNo 227
  title `Page 227`
  content obj_root_law_sections_227_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_227_footnotes
  sourcePage 227
obj_root_law_sections_227_content:
  string
  line 227
  line `( B ) where the assessee being a company, firm, association of persons or Hindu undivided`
  line `family, or any director of such company, partner of such firm or member of the association or`
  line `family, or any relative of such director, partner or member, has a substantial interest in the`
  line `business or profession of that person.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, a person shall be deemed to have a substantial`
  line `interest in a business or profession, if, —`
  line `( a ) in a case where the business or profession is carried on by a company, such person is, at`
  line `any time during the previous year, the beneficial owner of shares (not being shares entitled to a`
  line `fixed rate of dividend whether with or without a right to participate in profits) carrying not less`
  line `than twenty per cent of the voting power; and`
  line `( b ) in any other case, such person is, at any time during the previous year, beneficially`
  line `entitled to not less than twenty per cent of the profits of such business or profession.`
  line `1 [( 3 ) Where the assessee incurs any expenditure in respect of which a payment or aggregate of`
  line `payments made to a person in a day, otherwise than by an account payee cheque drawn on a bank or`
  line `account payee bank draft, 2 [ or use of electronic clearing system through a bank account, exceeds ten thousand`
  line `rupees ], no deduction shall be allowed in respect of such expenditure.`
  line `( 3A ) Where an allowance has been made in the assessment for any year in respect of any liability`
  line `incurred by the assessee for any expenditure and subsequently during any previous year (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as subsequent year) the assessee makes payment in respect thereof, otherwise than by an`
  line `account payee cheque drawn on a bank or account payee bank draft 3 [or use of electronic clearing system`
  line `through a bank account], the payment so made shall be deemed to be the profits and gains of business or`
  line `profession and accordingly chargeable to income-tax as income of the subsequent year if the payment or`
  line `aggregate of payments made to a person in a day, exceeds 4 [ ten thousand rupees ]:`
  line `Provided that no disallowance shall be made and no payment shall be deemed to be the profits and`
  line `gains of business or profession under sub-section ( 3 ) and this sub-section where a payment or aggregate`
  line `of payments made to a person in a day, otherwise than by an account payee cheque drawn on a bank or`
  line `account payee bank draft, 2 [ or use of electronic clearing system through a bank account, exceeds ten thousand`
  line `rupees ], in such cases and under such circumstances as may be prescribed, having regard to the nature and`
  line `extent of banking facilities available, considerations of business expediency and other relevant factors:]`
  line `5 [Provided further that in the case of payment made for plying, hiring or leasing goods carriages, the`
  line `provisions of sub-sections ( 3 ) and ( 3A ) shall have effect as if for the words 4 [ ten thousand rupees ], the`
  line `words “thirty - five thousand rupees” had been substituted.]`
  line `6 [( 4 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any`
  line `contract, where any payment in respect of any expenditure has to be made by 7 [an account payee cheque`
  line `drawn on a bank or account payee bank draft] 3 [or use of electronic clearing system through a bank`
  line `account] in order that such expenditure may not be disallowed as a deduction under sub-section ( 3 ), then`
  line `the payment may be made by such cheque or draft; 8 [or electronic clearing system] and where the`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 11, for sub-section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 15, for “exceeds twenty thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2018).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for “ twenty thousand rupees ” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2018).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-10-2009).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 14 of 1969, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1969).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 9, for the words “a crossed cheque drawn on a bank or by a crossed bank draft”`
  line `(w.e.f. 13-7-2006).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 15 (w.e.f 1-4-2018).`
