obj_root_law_sections_228_content:
  string
  line 228
  line `payment is so made or tendered, no person shall be allowed to raise, in any suit or other proceeding, a`
  line `plea based on the ground that the payment was not made or tendered in cash or in any other manner.]`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `2 [( 7 ) ( a ) Subject to the provisions of clause ( b ), no deduction shall be allowed in respect of any`
  line `provision (whether called as such or by any other name) made by the assessee for the payment of gratuity`
  line `to his employees on their retirement or on termination of their employment for any reason.`
  line `( b ) Nothing in clause ( a ) shall apply in relation to any provision made by the assessee for the purpose`
  line `of payment of a sum by way of any contribution towards an approved gratuity fund, or for the purpose of`
  line `payment of any gratuity, that has become payable during the previous year.`
  line `Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that where any provision made by the`
  line `assessee for the payment of gratuity to his employees on their retirement or termination of their`
  line `employment for any reason has been allowed as a deduction in computing the income of the assessee for`
  line `any assessment year, any sum paid out of such provision by way of contribution towards an approved`
  line `gratuity fund or by way of gratuity to any employee shall not be allowed as a deduction in computing the`
  line `income of the assessee of the previous year in which the sum is so paid.]`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 [( 9 ) No deduction shall be allowed in respect of any sum paid by the assessee as an employer`
  line `towards the setting up or formation of, or as contribution to, any fund, trust, company, association of`
  line `persons, body of individuals, society registered under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860),`
  line `or other institution for any purpose, except where such sum is so paid, for the purposes and to the extent`
  line `provided by or under clause ( iv ) 5 [or clause ( iva )] or clause ( v ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 36, or as`
  line `required by or under any other law for the time being in force.`
  line `( 10 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 9 ), where the 6 [Assessing Officer] is`
  line `satisfied that the fund, trust, company, association of persons, body of individuals, society or other`
  line `institution referred to in that sub-section has, before the 1st day of March, 1984, bona fide laid out or`
  line `expended any expenditure (not being in the nature of capital expenditure) wholly and exclusively for the`
  line `welfare of the employees of the assessee referred to in sub-section ( 9 ) out of the sum referred to in that`
  line `sub-section, the amount of such expenditure shall, in case no deduction has been allowed to the assessee`
  line `in respect of such sum and subject to the other provisions of this Act, be deducted in computing the`
  line `income referred to in section 28 of the assessee of the previous year in which such expenditure is so laid`
  line `out or expended, as if such expenditure had been laid out or expended by the assessee.`
  line `( 11 ) Where the assessee has, before the 1st day of March, 1984, paid any sum to any fund, trust,`
  line `company, association of persons, body of individuals, society or other institution referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 9 ), then, notwithstanding anything contained in any other law or in any instrument, he shall`
  line `be entitled —`
  line `( i ) to claim that so much of the amount paid by him as has not been laid out or expended by such`
  line `fund, trust, company, association of persons, body of individuals, society or other institution (such`
  line `amount being hereinafter referred to as the unutilised amount) be repaid to him, and where any claim`
  line `is so made, the unutilised amount shall be repaid, as soon as may be, to him;`
  line `1. Sub-sections ( 5 ) and ( 6 ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 23, for sub-section ( 7 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `3. Sub-section ( 8 ) omitted by Act 32 of 1985, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-1986).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-1980).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-2012).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 for “income - tax officer”(w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
