obj_root_law_sections_229_content:
  string
  line 229
  line `( ii ) to claim that any asset, being land, building, machinery, plant or furniture acquired or`
  line `constructed by the fund, trust, company, association of persons, body of individuals, society or other`
  line `institution out of the sum paid by the assessee, be transferred to him, and where any claim is so made,`
  line `such asset shall be transferred, as soon as may be, to him.]`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `2 [( 13 ) No deduction or allowance shall be allowed in respect of any marked to market loss or other`
  line `expected loss, except as allowable under clause ( xviii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 36.]`
  line `41. Profits chargeable to tax. — 3 [( 1 ) Where an allowance or deduction has been made in the`
  line `assessment for any year in respect of loss, expenditure or trading liability incurred by the assessee`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as the first-mentioned person) and subsequently during any previous year, —`
  line `( a ) the first-mentioned person has obtained, whether in cash or in any other manner whatsoever,`
  line `any amount in respect of such loss or expenditure or some benefit in respect of such trading liability`
  line `by way of remission or cessation thereof, the amount obtained by such person or the value of benefit`
  line `accruing to him shall be deemed to be profits and gains of business or profession and accordingly`
  line `chargeable to income-tax as the income of that previous year, whether the business or profession in`
  line `respect of which the allowance or deduction has been made is in existence in that year or not; or`
  line `( b ) the successor in business has obtained, whether in cash or in any other manner whatsoever,`
  line `any amount in respect of which loss or expenditure was incurred by the first-mentioned person or`
  line `some benefit in respect of the trading liability referred to in clause ( a ) by way of remission or`
  line `cessation thereof, the amount obtained by the successor in business or the value of benefit accruing to`
  line `the successor in business shall be deemed to be profits and gains of the business or profession, and`
  line `accordingly chargeable to income-tax as the income of that previous year.`
  line `4 [ Explanation 1. — For the purposes of this sub- section, the expression “loss or expenditure or some`
  line `benefit in resp ect of any such trading liability by way of remission or cessation thereof” shall include the`
  line `remission or cessation of any liability by a unilateral act by the first mentioned person under clause ( a ) or`
  line `the successor in business under clause ( b ) of that sub-section by way of writing off such liability in his`
  line accounts.]
  line `Explanation 5 [2] — For the purposes of this sub- section, “successor in business” means,—`
  line `( i ) where there has been an amalgamation of a company with another company, the`
  line `amalgamated company;`
  line `( ii ) where the first-mentioned person is succeeded by any other person in that business or`
  line `profession, the other person;`
  line `( iii ) where a firm carrying on a business or profession is succeeded by another firm, the other`
  line firm;]
  line `6 [( iv ) where there has been a demerger, the resulting company.]`
  line `7 [( 2 ) Where any building, machinery, plant or furniture, —`
  line `( a ) which is owned by the assessee;`
  line `1. Sub-section ( 12 ) omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993.)`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 11 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 18, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-1997).`
  line `5. Explanation renumbered as Explanation2 thereof by s. 16, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1997).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
