obj_root_law_sections_230_content:
  string
  line 230
  line `( b ) in respect of which depreciation is claimed under clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 32;`
  line and
  line `( c ) which was or has been used for the purposes of business,`
  line `is sold, discarded, demolished or destroyed and the moneys payable in respect of such building,`
  line `machinery, plant or furniture, as the case may be, together with the amount of scrap value, if any, exceeds`
  line `the written down value, so much of the excess as does not exceed the difference between the actual cost`
  line `and the written down value shall be chargeable to income-tax as income of the business of the previous`
  line `year in which the moneys payable for the building, machinery, plant or furniture became due.`
  line `Explanation. — Where the moneys payable in respect of the building, machinery, plant or furniture`
  line `referred to in this sub-section become due in a previous year in which the business for the purpose of`
  line `which the building, machinery, plant or furniture was being used is no longer in existence, the provision`
  line `of this sub-section shall apply as if the business is in existence in that previous year.]`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `( 3 ) Where an asset representing expenditure of a capital nature on scientific research within the`
  line `meaning of 2 [clause ( iv ) of sub-section ( 1 ), or clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 2B ), of section 35], read with`
  line `clause ( 4 ) of section 43, is sold, without having been used for other purposes, and the proceeds of the sale`
  line `together with the total amount of the deductions made under clause ( i ) 3 [or, as the case may be, the`
  line `amount of the deduction under clause ( ia ) of sub-section ( 2 ), or clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 2B ), of section`
  line `35] exceed the amount of the capital expenditure, the excess or the amount of the deductions so made,`
  line `whichever is the less, shall be chargeable to income-tax as income of the business or profession of the`
  line `previous year in which the sale took place.`
  line `Explanation. — Where the moneys payable in respect of any asset referred to in this sub-section`
  line `become due in a previous year in which the business is no longer in existence, the provisions of this`
  line `sub-section shall apply as if the business is in existence in that previous year.`
  line `( 4 ) Where a deduction has been allowed in respect of a bad debt or part of debt under the provisions`
  line `of clause ( vii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 36, then, if the amount subsequently recovered on any such`
  line `debt or part is greater than the difference between the debt or part of debt and the amount so allowed, the`
  line `excess shall be deemed to be profits and gains of business or profession, and accordingly chargeable to`
  line `income-tax as the income of the previous year in which it is recovered, whether the business or profession`
  line `in respect of which the deduction has been allowed is in existence in that year or not.`
  line `4 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of sub-section ( 3 ), —`
  line `( 1 ) “moneys payable” in respect of any building, machinery, plant or furniture includes—`
  line `( a ) any insurance, salvage or compensation moneys payable in respect thereof;`
  line `( b ) where the building, machinery, plant or furniture is sold, the price for which it is sold,`
  line `so, however, that where the actual cost of a motor car is, in accordance with the proviso to clause ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 43, taken to be twenty-five thousand rupees, the moneys payable in respect of such motor car shall`
  line `be taken to be a sum which bears to the amount for which the motor car is sold or, as the case may be, the`
  line `amount of any insurance, salvage or compensation moneys payable in respect thereof (including the`
  line `amount of scrap value, if any) the same proportion as the amount of twenty-five thousand rupees bears to`
  line `1. Sub-section ( 2A ) omitted by Act 46 of 1986, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 11, for the words, brackets and figures “clause ( iv ) of subsection ( 1 ) of section 35”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1981).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for “clause ( ia ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 35” (w.e.f. 1 -4- 1981). Earlier Quoted portion “or, as the`
  line `case may be, the amount of the deduction under clause ( ia )” inserted by Act 20 of 1967, s. 33 and the Third Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f 1-4-1968).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 7, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
