obj_root_law_sections_231_content:
  string
  line 231
  line `the actual cost of the motor car to the assessee as it would have been computed before applying the said`
  line proviso;
  line `( 2 ) “sold” includes a transfer by way of exchange or a compulsory acquisition under any law for`
  line `the time being in force but does not include a transfer, in a scheme of amalgamation, of any asset by`
  line `the amalgamating company to the amalgamated company where the amalgamated company is an`
  line `Indian company.]`
  line `1 [( 4A ) Where a deduction has been allowed in respect of any special reserve created and maintained`
  line `under clause ( viii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 36, any amount subsequently withdrawn from such special`
  line `reserve shall be deemed to be the profits and gains of business or profession and accordingly be`
  line `chargeable to income-tax as the income of the previous year in which such amount is withdrawn.`
  line `Explanation. — Where any amount is withdrawn from the special reserve in a previous year in which`
  line `the business is no longer in existence, the provisions of this sub-section shall apply as if the business is in`
  line `existence in that previous year.]`
  line `( 5 ) Where the business or profession referred to in this section is no longer in existence and`
  line `there is income chargeable to tax under sub-section ( 1 ), 2 *** sub-section ( 3 ), 3 [sub-section ( 4 ) or`
  line `sub-section ( 4A )] in respect of that business or profession, any loss, not being a loss sustained in`
  line `speculation 4 *** business, which arose in that business or profession during the previous year in which it`
  line `ceased to exist and which could not be set off against any other income of that previous year shall, so far`
  line `as may be, be set off against the income chargeable to tax under the sub-sections aforesaid.`
  line `5 [( 6 ) References in sub-section ( 3 ) to any other provision of this Act which has been amended or`
  line `omitted by the Direct Tax Laws (Amendment) Act, 1987 shall, notwithstanding such amendment or`
  line `omission, be construed, for the purposes of that sub-section, as if such amendment or omission had not`
  line `been made.]`
  line `42. Special provision for deductions in the case of business for prospecting, etc., for mineral`
  line `oil. — 6 [( 1 )] For the purpose of computing the profits or gains of any business consisting of the`
  line `prospecting for or extraction or production of mineral oils in relation to which the Central Government`
  line `has entered into an agreement with any person for the 7 [association or participation of the Central`
  line `Government or any person authorised by it in such business] (which agreement has been laid on the Table`
  line `of each House of Parliament), there shall be made in lieu of, or in addition to, the allowances admissible`
  line `under this Act, such allowances as are specified in the agreement in relation —`
  line `( a ) to expenditure by way of infructuous or abortive exploration expenses in respect of any area`
  line `surrendered prior to the beginning of commercial production by the assessee;`
  line `( b ) after the beginning of commercial production, to expenditure incurred by the assessee,`
  line `whether before or after such commercial production, in respect of drilling or exploration activities or`
  line `services or in respect of physical assets used in that connection, except assets on which allowance for`
  line `depreciation is admissible under section 32: 8 ***`
  line `9 [Provided that in relation to any agreement entered into after the 31st day of March, 1981, this`
  line `clause shall have effect subject to the modification that the words and figure s “except assets on which`
  line `allowance for depreciation is admissible under section 32” had been omitted; and]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `2. The words, brackets and figures “sub -section ( 2 ), sub-section ( 2A )”omitted by Act 46 of 1986, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 9, for “or sub -section ( 4 )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1998).`
  line `4. The words “or under the head Capital gains” omitted by Act 11 of 1987, s. 74 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 126(w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `6. Section 42 renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 21 of 1998, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 16 of 1981, s. 8, for “the association or participation in such business of the Central Government”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1981).`
  line `8. The word “and” omitted bys. 8, ibid.(w.e.f. 1-4-1981).`
  line `9. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1981)`
