obj_root_law_sections_232_content:
  string
  line 232
  line `( c ) to the depletion of mineral oil in the mining area in respect of the assessment year relevant to`
  line `the previous year in which commercial production is begun and for such succeeding year or years as`
  line `may be specified in the agreement;`
  line `and such allowances shall be computed and made in the manner specified in the agreement, the other`
  line `provisions of this Act being deemed for this purpose to have been modified to the extent necessary to give`
  line `effect to the terms of the agreement.`
  line `1 [( 2 ) Where the business of the assessee consisting of the prospecting for or extraction or production`
  line `of petroleum and natural gas is transferred wholly or partly or any interest in such business is transferred`
  line `in accordance with the agreement referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), subject to the provisions of the said`
  line `agreement and where the proceeds of the transfer (so far as they consist of capital sums) —`
  line `( a ) are less than the expenditure incurred remaining unallowed, a deduction equal to such`
  line `expenditure remaining unallowed, as reduced by the proceeds of transfer, shall be allowed in respect`
  line `of the previous year in which such business or interest, as the case may be, is transferred;`
  line `( b ) exceed the amount of the expenditure incurred remaining unallowed, so much of the excess as`
  line `does not exceed the difference between the expenditure incurred in connection with the business or to`
  line `obtain interest therein and the amount of such expenditure remaining unallowed, shall be chargeable`
  line `to income-tax as profits and gains of the business in the previous year in which the business or`
  line `interest therein, whether wholly or partly, had been transferred:`
  line `Provided that in a case where the provisions of this clause do not apply, the deduction to be allowed`
  line `for expenditure incurred remaining unallowed shall be arrived at by subtracting the proceeds of transfer`
  line `(so far as they consist of capital sums) from the expenditure remaining unallowed.`
  line `Explanation. — Where the business or interest in such business is transferred in a previous year in`
  line `which such business carried on by the assessee is no longer in existence, the provisions of this clause shall`
  line `apply as if the business is in existence in that previous year;`
  line `( c ) are not less than the amount of the expenditure incurred remaining unallowed, no deduction`
  line `for such expenditure shall be allowed in respect of the previous year in which the business or interest`
  line `in such business is transferred or in respect of any subsequent year or years:`
  line `2 [Provided that where in a scheme of amalgamation or demerger, the amalgamating or the`
  line `demerged company sells or otherwise transfers the business to the amalgamated or the resulting`
  line `company (being an Indian company), the provisions of this sub-section —`
  line `( i ) shall not apply in the case of the amalgamating or the demerged company; and`
  line `( ii ) shall, as far as may be, apply to the amalgamated or the resulting company as they would`
  line `have applied to the amalgamating or the demerged company if the latter had not transferred the`
  line `business or interest in the business.]]`
  line `3 [ Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, “mineral oil” includes petroleum and natural`
  line gas.]
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 25, for “the proviso” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2000).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 16 of 1981, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-1981).`
obj_root_law_sections_232_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_233:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-233
  sectionNo (233)
  orderNo 233
  title `Page 233`
  content obj_root_law_sections_233_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_233_footnotes
  sourcePage 233
obj_root_law_sections_233_content:
  string
  line 233
  line `43. Definitions of certain terms relevant to income from profits and gains of business or`
  line `profession. — In section 28 to 41 and in this section, unless the context otherwise requires —`
  line `( 1 ) “actual cost” means the actual cost of the assets to the assessee, reduced by that portion of the`
  line `cost thereof, if any, as has been met directly or indirectly by any other person or authority:`
  line `1 [Provided that where the actual cost of an asset, being a motor car which is acquired by the`
  line `assessee after the 31st day of March, 1967 2 [, but before the 1st day of March, 1975,] and is used`
  line `otherwise than in a business of running it on hire for tourists, exceeds twenty-five thousand rupees,`
  line `the excess of the actual cost over such amount shall be ignored, and the actual cost thereof shall be`
  line `taken to be twenty-five thousand rupees:]`
  line `3 [Provided further that where the assessee incurs any expenditure for acquisition of any asset or`
  line `part thereof in respect of which a payment or aggregate of payments made to a person in a day,`
  line `otherwise than by an account payee cheque drawn on a bank or an account payee bank draft or use of`
  line `electronic clearing system through a bank account, exceeds ten thousand rupees, such expenditure`
  line `shall be ignored for the purposes of determination of actual cost.]`
  line `Explanation 1. — Where an asset is used in the business after it ceases to be used for scientific`
  line `research related to that business and a deduction has to be made under 4 [clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 1 )]`
  line `of section 32 in respect of that asset, the actual cost of the asset to the assessee shall be the actual cost to`
  line `the assessee as reduced by the amount of any deduction allowed under clause ( iv ) of sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 35 or under any corresponding provision of the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922).`
  line `5 [ Explanation 1A. — Where a capital asset referred to in clause ( via ) of section 28 is used for the`
  line `purposes of business or profession, the actual cost of such asset to the assessee shall be the fair market`
  line `value which has been taken into account for the purposes of the said clause.]`
  line `6 [ Explanation 2. — Where an asset is acquired by the assessee by way of gift or inheritance, the actual`
  line `cost of the asset to the assessee shall be the actual cost to the previous owner, as reduced by —`
  line `( a ) the amount of depreciation actually allowed under this Act and the corresponding provisions`
  line `of the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922), in respect of any previous year relevant to the`
  line `assessment year commencing before the 1st day of April, 1988; and`
  line `( b ) the amount of depreciation that would have been allowable to the assessee for any assessment`
  line `year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 1988, as if the asset was the only asset in the`
  line `relevant block of assets.]`
  line `Explanation 3. — Where, before the date of acquisition by the assessee, the assets were at any time`
  line `used by any other person for the purposes of his business or profession and the 7 [Assessing Officer] is`
  line `satisfied that the main purpose of the transfer of such assets, directly or indirectly to the assessee, was the`
  line `reduction of a liability to income-tax (by claiming depreciation with reference to an enhanced cost), the`
  line `actual cost to the assessee shall be such an amount as the 7 [Assessing Officer] may, with the previous`
  line `approval of the 8 [Joint Commissioner], determine having regard to all the circumstances of the case.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 33 and the Third Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-1968).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 25 of 1975, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-1975).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 8, for “clause ( i ), clause ( ii ) or clause ( iii ) or sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 1A )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-`
  line `1988).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 8, for Explanation 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 3, for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
obj_root_law_sections_233_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_234:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-234
  sectionNo (234)
  orderNo 234
  title `Page 234`
  content obj_root_law_sections_234_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_234_footnotes
  sourcePage 234
obj_root_law_sections_234_content:
  string
  line 234
  line `1 [ Explanation 4. — Where any asset which had once belonged to the assessee and had been used by`
  line `him for the purposes of his business or profession and thereafter ceased to be his property by reason of`
  line `transfer or otherwise, is re-acquired by him, the actual cost to the assessee shall be —`
  line `( i ) the actual cost to him when he first acquired the asset as reduced by —`
  line `( a ) the amount of depreciation actually allowed to him under this Act or under the`
  line `corresponding provisions of the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922), in respect of any`
  line `previous year relevant to the assessment year commencing before the 1st day of April, 1988; and`
  line `( b ) the amount of depreciation that would have been allowable to the assessee for any`
  line `assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 1988, as if the asset was the only`
  line `asset in the relevant block of assets; or`
  line `( ii ) the actual price for which the asset is re-acquired by him,`
  line `whichever is less.]`
  line `2 [ Explanation 4A. — Where before the date of acquisition by the assessee (hereinafter referred to as`
  line `the first mentioned person), the assets were at any time used by any other person (hereinafter referred to`
  line `as the second mentioned person) for the purposes of his business or profession and depreciation`
  line `allowance has been claimed in respect of such assets in the case of the second mentioned person and such`
  line `person acquires on lease, hire or otherwise assets from the first mentioned person, then, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in Explanation 3, the actual cost of the transferred assets, in the case of first`
  line `mentioned person, shall be the same as the written down value of the said assets at the time of transfer`
  line `thereof by the second mentioned person.]`
  line `Explanation 5. — Where a building previously the property of the assessee is brought into use for the`
  line `purpose of the business or profession after the 28th day of February, 1946, the actual cost to the assessee`
  line `shall be the actual cost of the building to the assessee, as reduced by an amount equal to the depreciation`
  line `calculated at the rate in force on that date that would have been allowable had the building been used for`
  line `the aforesaid purposes since the date of its acquisition by the assessee.`
  line `3 [ Explanation 6. — When any capital asset is transferred by a holding company to its subsidiary`
  line `company or by a subsidiary company to its holding company, then, if the conditions of clause (iv) or, as`
  line `the case may be, of clause (v) of section 47 are satisfied, the actual cost of the transferred capital asset to`
  line `the transferee-company shall be taken to be the same as it would have been if the transferor-company had`
  line `continued to hold the capital asset for the purposes of its business.]`
  line `4 [ Explanation 7. — Where, in a scheme of amalgamation, any capital asset is transferred by the`
  line `amalgamating company to the amalgamated company and the amalgamated company is an Indian`
  line `company, the actual cost of the transferred capital asset to the amalgamated company shall be taken to be`
  line `the same as it would have been if the amalgamating company had continued to hold the capital asset for`
  line `the purposes of its own business.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 8, for Explanation 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-10-1996).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-1967).`
obj_root_law_sections_234_footnotes:
