  line
obj_root_law_sections_235:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-235
  sectionNo (235)
  orderNo 235
  title `Page 235`
  content obj_root_law_sections_235_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_235_footnotes
  sourcePage 235
obj_root_law_sections_235_content:
  string
  line 235
  line `1 [ Explanation 7A. — Where, in a demerger, any capital asset is transferred by the demerged company`
  line `to the resulting company and the resulting company is an Indian company, the actual cost of the`
  line `transferred capital asset to the resulting company shall be taken to be the same as it would have been if`
  line `the demerged company had continued to hold the capital asset for the purpose of its own business:`
  line `Provided that such actual cost shall not exceed the written down value of such capital asset in the`
  line `hands of the demerged company.]`
  line `2 [ Explanation 8. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that where any amount is paid or is`
  line `payable as interest in connection with the acquisition of an asset, so much of such amount as is relatable`
  line `to any period after such asset is first put to use shall not be included, and shall be deemed never to have`
  line `been included, in the actual cost of such asset.]`
  line `3 [ Explanation 9. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that where an asset is or has been`
  line `acquired on or after the 1st day of March, 1994 by an assessee, the actual cost of asset shall be reduced by`
  line `the amount of duty of excise or the additional duty leviable under section 3 of the Customs Tariff Act,`
  line `1975 (51 of 1975) in respect of which a claim of credit has been made and allowed under the Central`
  line `Excise Rules, 1944.]`
  line `4 [E xplanation 10. — Where a portion of the cost of an asset acquired by the assessee has been met`
  line `directly or indirectly by the Central Government or a State Government or any authority established under`
  line `any law or by any other person, in the form of a subsidy or grant or reimbursement (by whatever name`
  line `called), then, so much of the cost as is relatable to such subsidy or grant or reimbursement shall not be`
  line `included in the actual cost of the asset to the assessee:`
  line `Provided that where such subsidy or grant or reimbursement is of such nature that it cannot be`
  line `directly relatable to the asset acquired, so much of the amount which bears to the total subsidy or`
  line `reimbursement or grant the same proportion as such asset bears to all the assets in respect of or with`
  line `reference to which the subsidy or grant or reimbursement is so received, shall not be included in the`
  line `actual cost of the asset to the assessee.]`
  line `1 [ Explanation 11. — Where an asset which was acquired outside India by an assessee, being a non-`
  line `resident, is brought by him to India and used for the purposes of his business or profession, the actual cost`
  line `of the asset to the assessee shall be the actual cost to the assessee, as reduced by an amount equal to the`
  line `amount of depreciation calculated at the rate in force that would have been allowable had the asset been`
  line `used in India for the said purposes since the date of its acquisition by the assessee.]`
  line `5 [ Explanation 12. — Where any capital asset is acquired by the assessee under a scheme for`
  line `corporatisation of a recognised stock exchange in India, approved by the Securities and Exchange Board`
  line `of India established under section 3 of the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of`
  line `1992), the actual cost of the asset shall be deemed to be the amount which would have been regarded as`
  line `actual cost had there been no such corporatization.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27of 1999, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 1986, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-1994).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 18, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
