obj_root_law_sections_236_content:
  string
  line 236
  line `1 [ Explanation 13. — The actual cost of any capital asset on which deduction has been allowed or is`
  line `allowable to the assessee under section 35AD, shall be treated as ' nil ', —`
  line `( a ) in the case of such assessee; and`
  line `( b ) in any other case if the capital asset is acquired or received, —`
  line `( i ) by way of gift or will or an irrevocable trust;`
  line `( ii ) on any distribution on liquidation of the company; and`
  line `( iii ) by such mode of transfer as is referred to in clauses ( i ), ( iv ), ( v ), ( vi ), ( vib ), 2 [( xiii ), ( xiiib )`
  line `and ( xiv )] of section 47:]`
  line `3 [Provided that where any capital asset in respect of which deduction or part of deduction allowed`
  line `under section 35AD is deemed to be the income of the assessee in accordance with the provisions of sub-`
  line `section ( 7B ) of the said section, the actual cost of the asset to the assessee shall be the actual cost to the`
  line `assessee, as reduced by an amount equal to the amount of depreciation calculated at the rate in force that`
  line `would have been allowable had the asset been used for the purpose of business since the date of its`
  line acquisition.]
  line `( 2 ) “paid” means actually paid or incurred according to the method of accounting upon the basis of`
  line `which the profits or gains are computed under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession”;`
  line `( 3 ) “plant” includes ships, vehicles, books, scientific app aratus and surgical equipment used for the`
  line `purposes of the business or profession 4 [but does not include tea bushes or livestock] 5 [or buildings or`
  line `furniture and fittings];`
  line `( 4 ) ( i ) “scientific research” means any activities for the extension of knowledge in the fields of natural`
  line `or applied science including agriculture, animal husbandry or fisheries;`
  line `( ii ) references to expenditure incurred on scientific research include all expenditure incurred for the`
  line `prosecution, or the provision of facilities for the prosecution, of scientific research, but do not include any`
  line `expenditure incurred in the acquisition of rights in, or arising out of, scientific research;`
  line `( iii ) references to scientific research related to a business or class of business include —`
  line `( a ) any scientific research which may lead to or facilitate an extension of that business or, as the`
  line `case may be, all businesses of that class;`
  line `( b ) any scientific research of a medical nature which has a special relation to the welfare of`
  line `workers employed in that business or, as the case may be, all businesses of that class;`
  line `( 5 ) “speculative transaction” means a transaction in which a contract for the purchase or sale of any`
  line `commodity, including stocks and shares, is periodically or ultimately settled otherwise than by the actual`
  line `delivery or transfer of the commodity or scrips:`
  line `Provided that for the purposes of this clause —`
  line `( a ) a contract in respect of raw materials or merchandise entered into by a person in the course of`
  line `his manufacturing or merchanting business to guard against loss through future price fluctuations in`
  line `respect of his contracts for actual delivery of goods manufactured by him or merchandise sold by`
  line `him; or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 13, for “( xiii ) and ( xiv )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2011).`
  line `3. The proviso ins by Act 7 of 2017, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_236_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_237:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-237
  sectionNo (237)
  orderNo 237
  title `Page 237`
  content obj_root_law_sections_237_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_237_footnotes
  sourcePage 237
obj_root_law_sections_237_content:
  string
  line 237
  line `( b ) a contract in respect of stocks and shares entered into by a dealer or investor therein to guard`
  line `against loss in his holdings of stocks and shares through price fluctuations; or`
  line `( c ) a contract entered into by a member of a forward market or a stock exchange in the course of`
  line `any transaction in the nature of jobbing or arbitrage to guard against loss which may arise in the`
  line `ordinary course of his business as such member; 1 [or]`
  line `1 [( d ) an eligible transaction in respect of trading in derivatives referred to in clause 2 [( ac )] of`
  line `section 2 of the Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956) carried out in a recognised`
  line `stock exchange; 3 [or]]`
  line `3 [( e ) an eligible transaction in respect of trading in commodity derivatives carried out in a`
  line `recognised association 4 [, which is chargeable to commodities transaction tax under Chapter VII of`
  line `the Finance Act, 2013 (17 of 2013),]`
  line `shall not be deemed to be a speculative transaction.`
  line `5 [Provided further that for the purposes of clause ( e ) of the first proviso, in respect of trading in`
  line `agricultural commodity derivatives, the requirement of chargeability of commodity transaction tax under`
  line `Chapter VII of the Finance Act, 2013 shall not apply.]`
  line `1 [ 6 [ Explanation 1]. — For the purposes of 7 [clause ( d )], the expressions —`
  line `( i ) “eligible transaction” means any transaction,—`
  line `( A ) carried out electronically on screen-based systems through a stock broker or sub-broker or`
  line `such other intermediary registered under section 12 of the Securities and Exchange Board of`
  line `India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992) in accordance with the provisions of the Securities Contracts`
  line `(Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956) or the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15`
  line `of 1992) or the Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996) and the rules, regulations or bye-laws made`
  line `or directions issued under those Acts or by banks or mutual funds on a recognised stock`
  line `exchange; and`
  line `( B ) which is supported by a time stamped contract note issued by such stock broker or`
  line `sub-broker or such other intermediary to every client indicating in the contract note the unique`
  line `client identity number allotted under any Act referred to in sub-clause ( A ) and permanent account`
  line `number allotted under this Act;`
  line `( ii ) “recognised stock exchange” means a recognised stock exchange as referred to in clause ( f ) of`
  line `section 2 of the Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956) and which fulfils such`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed and notified by the Central Government for this purpose.]`
  line `8 [ Explanation 2. — For the purposes of clause ( e ), the expressions —`
  line `( i ) “commodity derivative” shall have the meaning as assigned to it in Chapter VII of the`
  line `Finance Act, 2013;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 11, for “( aa )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 15, for “recognised association” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2014).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
  line `6. The Explanation renumbered as Explanation 1 by Act 17 of 2013, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., “this clause” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `8. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_237_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_238:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-238
  sectionNo (238)
  orderNo 238
  title `Page 238`
  content obj_root_law_sections_238_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_238_footnotes
  sourcePage 238
obj_root_law_sections_238_content:
  string
  line 238
  line `( ii ) “eligible transaction” means any transaction,—`
  line `( A ) carried out electronically on screen-based systems through member or an intermediary,`
  line `registered under the bye-laws, rules and regulations of the recognised association for trading in`
  line `commodity derivative in accordance with the provisions of the Forward Contracts (Regulation)`
  line `Act, 1952 (74 of 1952) and the rules, regulations or bye-laws made or directions issued under that`
  line `Act on a recognised association; and`
  line `( B ) which is supported by a time stamped contract note issued by such member or`
  line `intermediary to every client indicating in the contract note, the unique client identity number`
  line `allotted under the Act, rules, regulations or bye-laws referred to in sub-clause ( A ), unique trade`
  line `number and permanent account number allotted under this Act;`
  line `( iii ) “recognised association” means a recognised association as referred to in clause ( j ) of`
  line `section 2 of the Forward Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1952 (74 of 1952) and which fulfils such`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed and is notified by the Central Government for this purpose;]`
  line `( 6 ) “written down value” means—`
  line `( a ) in the case of assets acquired in the previous year, the actual cost to the assessee;`
  line `( b ) in the case of assets acquired before the previous year, the actual cost to the assessee less all`
  line `depreciation actually allowed to him under this Act, or under the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of`
  line `1922), or any Act repealed by that Act, or under any executive orders issued when the Indian Income-`
  line `tax Act, 1886 (2 of 1886), was in force:`
  line `1 [Provided that in determining the written down value in respect of buildings, machinery or plant`
  line `for the purposes of clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 32, “depreciation actually allowed” shall`
  line `not include depreciation allowed under sub-clauses ( a ), ( b ) and ( c ) of clause ( vi ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 10 of the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922), where such depreciation was not`
  line `deductible in determining the written down value for the purposes of the said clause ( vi );]`
  line `2 [( c ) in the case of any block of assets, —`
  line `( i ) in respect of any previous year relevant to the assessment year commencing on the 1st day`
  line `of April, 1988, the aggregate of the written down values of all the assets falling within that block`
  line `of assets at the beginning of the previous year and adjusted, —`
  line `( A ) by the increase by the actual cost of any asset falling within that block, acquired`
  line `during the previous year;`
  line `( B ) by the reduction of the moneys payable in respect of any asset falling within that`
  line `block, which is sold or discarded or demolished or destroyed during that previous year`
  line `together with the amount of the scrap value, if any, so, however, that the amount of such`
  line `reduction does not exceed the written down value as so increased; and`
  line `3 [( C ) in the case of a slump sale, decrease by the actual cost of the asset falling within`
  line `that block as reduced —`
  line `( a ) by the amount of depreciation actually allowed to him under this Act or under the`
  line `corresponding provisions of the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922) in respect of`
  line `any previous year relevant to the assessment year commencing before the 1st day of`
  line `April, 1988; and`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 1965, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_238_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_239:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-239
  sectionNo (239)
  orderNo 239
  title `Page 239`
  content obj_root_law_sections_239_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_239_footnotes
  sourcePage 239
obj_root_law_sections_239_content:
  string
  line 239
  line `( b ) by the amount of depreciation that would have been allowable to the assessee for`
  line `any assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 1988 as if the asset was`
  line `the only asset in the relevant block of assets, so, however, that the amount of such`
  line `decrease does not exceed the written down value;]`
  line `( ii ) in respect of any previous year relevant to the assessment year commencing on or after`
  line `the 1st day of April, 1989, the written down value of that block of assets in the immediately`
  line `preceding previous year as reduced by the depreciation actually allowed in respect of that block`
  line `of assets in relation to the said preceding previous year and as further adjusted by the increase or`
  line `the reduction referred to in item ( i ).]`
  line `Explanation 1. — When in a case of succession in business or profession, an assessment is made on`
  line `the successor under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 170 the written down 1 [value of any asset or any block of`
  line `assets] shall be the amount which would have been taken as its written down value if the assessment had`
  line `been made directly on the person succeeded to.`
  line `2 [ Explanation 2. — Where in any previous year, any block of assets is transferred, —`
  line `( a ) by a holding company to its subsidiary company or by a subsidiary company to its holding`
  line `company and the conditions of clause ( iv ) or, as the case may be, of clause ( v ) of section 47 are`
  line `satisfied; or`
  line `( b ) by the amalgamating company to the amalgamated company in a scheme of amalgamation,`
  line `and the amalgamated company is an Indian company,`
  line `then, notwithstanding anything contained in clause ( 1 ), the actual cost of the block of assets in the case of`
  line `the transferee-company or the amalgamated company, as the case may be, shall be the written down value`
  line `of the block of assets as in the case of the transferor-company or the amalgamating company for the`
  line `immediately preceding previous year as reduced by the amount of depreciation actually allowed in`
  line `relation to the said preceding previous year.]`
  line `3 [ Explanation 2A. — Where in any previous year, any asset forming part of a block of assets is`
  line `transferred by a demerged company to the resulting company, then, notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in clause ( 1 ), the written down value of the block of assets of the demerged company for the immediately`
  line `preceding previous year shall be reduced by the 4 [written down value of the assets] transferred to the`
  line `resulting company pursuant to the demerger.`
  line `Explanation 2B. — Where in a previous year, any asset forming part of a block of assets is transferred`
  line `by a demerged company to the resulting company, then, notwithstanding anything contained in clause ( 1 ),`
  line `the written down value of the block of assets in the case of the resulting company shall be the 5 [written`
  line `down value of the transferred assets 6 ***] of the demerged company immediately before the demerger.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 8, for “any asset” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for Explanation 2 and Explanation 2A (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 19, for “book value of the assets” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2000 ).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for “value of the assets as appearing in the books of account” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2000).`
  line `6. The words “as appearing in the books of account” omitted b y Act 32 of 2003, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_239_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_240:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-240
  sectionNo (240)
  orderNo 240
  title `Page 240`
  content obj_root_law_sections_240_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_240_footnotes
  sourcePage 240
obj_root_law_sections_240_content:
  string
  line 240
  line `1 [ Explanation 2C. — Where in any previous year, any block of assets is transferred by a private`
  line `company or unlisted public company to a limited liability partnership and the conditions specified in the`
  line `proviso to clause ( xiiib ) of section 47 are satisfied, then, notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `clause ( 1 ), the actual cost of the block of assets in the case of the limited liability partnership shall be the`
  line `written down value of the block of assets as in the case of the said company on the date of conversion of`
  line `the company into the limited liability partnership.]`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `Explanation 3. — Any allowance in respect of any depreciation carried forward under sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 32 shall be deemed to be depreciation “actually allowed”.`
  line `3 [ Explanation 4. —For the purposes of this clause, the expressions “moneys payable” and “sold” shall`
  line `have the same meanings as in the Explanation below sub-section ( 4 ) of section 41.]`
  line `4 [ Explanation 5. — Where in a previous year, any asset forming part of a block of assets is transferred`
  line `by a recognised stock exchange in India to a company under a scheme for corporatisation approved by the`
  line `Securities and Exchange Board of India established under section 3 of the Securities and Exchange Board`
  line `of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992), the written down value of the block of assets in the case of such company`
  line `shall be the written down value of the transferred assets immediately before such transfer.]`
  line `5 [ Explanation 6. — Where an assessee was not required to compute his total income for the purposes`
  line `of this Act for any previous year or years preceding the previous year relevant to the assessment year`
  line `under consideration, —`
  line `( a ) the actual cost of an asset shall be adjusted by the amount attributable to the revaluation of`
  line `such asset, if any, in the books of account;`
  line `( b ) the total amount of depreciation on such asset, provided in the books of account of the`
  line `assessee in respect of such previous year or years preceding the previous year relevant to the`
  line `assessment year under consideration shall be deemed to be the depreciation actually allowed under`
  line `this Act for the purposes of this clause; and`
  line `( c ) the depreciation actually allowed under clause ( b ) shall be adjusted by the amount of`
  line `depreciation attributable to such revaluation of the asset.]`
  line `6 [ Explanation 7. — For the purposes of this clause, where the income of an assessee is derived, in part`
  line `from agriculture and in part from business chargeable to income- tax under the head “Profits and gains of`
  line `business or profession”, for computi ng the written down value of assets acquired before the previous year,`
  line `the total amount of depreciation shall be computed as if the entire income is derived from the business of`
  line `the assessee under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession” and the depreciation so`
  line `computed shall be deemed to be the depreciation actually allowed under this Act.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-2011).`
  line `2. The proviso omitted by Act 10 of 2000, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 8 (w.e.f 1-4-1988).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
