  title `Page 241`
  content obj_root_law_sections_241_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_241_footnotes
  sourcePage 241
obj_root_law_sections_241_content:
  string
  line 241
  line `1 [ 43A. Special provisions consequential to changes in rate of exchange ofcurrency. —`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, where an assessee has acquired`
  line `any asset in any previous year from a country outside India for the purposes of his business or profession`
  line `and, in consequence of a change in the rate of exchange during any previous year after the acquisition of`
  line `such asset, there is an increase or reduction in the liability of the assessee as expressed in Indian currency`
  line `(as compared to the liability existing at the time of acquisition of the asset) at the time of making`
  line `payment —`
  line `( a ) towards the whole or a part of the cost of the asset; or`
  line `( b ) towards repayment of the whole or a part of the moneys borrowed by him from any person,`
  line `directly or indirectly, in any foreign currency specifically for the purpose of acquiring the asset along`
  line `with interest, if any,`
  line `the amount by which the liability as aforesaid is so increased or reduced during such previous year and`
  line `which is taken into account at the time of making the payment, irrespective of the method of accounting`
  line `adopted by the assessee, shall be added to, or, as the case may be, deducted from —`
  line `( i ) the actual cost of the asset as defined in clause ( 1 ) of section 43; or`
  line `( ii ) the amount of expenditure of a capital nature referred to in clause ( iv ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 35; or`
  line `( iii ) the amount of expenditure of a capital nature referred to in section 35A; or`
  line `( iv ) the amount of expenditure of a capital nature referred to in clause ( ix ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 36; or`
  line `( v ) the cost of acquisition of a capital asset (not being a capital asset referred to in section 50) for`
  line `the purposes of section 48,`
  line `and the amount arrived at after such addition or deduction shall be taken to be the actual cost of the asset`
  line `or the amount of expenditure of a capital nature or, as the case may be, the cost of acquisition of the`
  line `capital asset as aforesaid:`
  line `Provided that where an addition to or deduction from the actual cost or expenditure or cost of`
  line `acquisition has been made under this section, as it stood immediately before its substitution by the`
  line `Finance Act, 2002, on account of an increase or reduction in the liability as aforesaid, the amount to be`
  line `added to, or, as the case may be, deducted under this section from, the actual cost or expenditure or cost`
  line `of acquisition at the time of making the payment shall be so adjusted that the total amount added to, or, as`
  line `the case may be, deducted from, the actual cost or expenditure or cost of acquisition, is equal to the`
  line `increase or reduction in the aforesaid liability taken into account at the time of making payment.`
  line `Explanation 1. — In this section, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “rate of exchange” means the rate of exchange determined or recognised by the Central`
  line `Government for the conversion of Indian currency into foreign currency or foreign currency into`
  line `Indian currency;`
  line `( b ) “foreign currency” and “Indian currency” have the meanings respectively assigned to them in`
  line `section 2 of the Foreign Exchange Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999).`
  line `Explanation 2. — Where the whole or any part of the liability aforesaid is met, not by the assessee,`
  line `but, directly or indirectly, by any other person or authority, the liability so met shall not be taken into`
  line `account for the purposes of this section.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 21, for section 43A (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
