obj_root_law_sections_244_content:
  string
  line 244
  line `1 [ Explanation 3C. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that a deduction of any sum,`
  line `being interest payable under clause ( d ) of this section, shall be allowed if such interest has been actually`
  line `paid and any interest referred to in that clause which has been converted into a loan or borrowing shall not`
  line `be deemed to have been actually paid.]`
  line `2 [ Explanation 3D. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that a deduction of any sum,`
  line `being interest payable under clause ( e ) of this section, shall be allowed if such interest has been actually`
  line `paid and any interest referred to in that clause which has been converted into a loan or advance shall not`
  line `be deemed to have been actually paid.]`
  line `3 [ Explanation 4. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “public financial institutions” shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 4A of the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line `4 [( aa ) “scheduled bank” shall have the meaning assigned to it in the Explanation to clause ( iii ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 5 ) of section 11;]`
  line `( b ) “State financial corporation” means a financial corporation established under section 3 or`
  line `section 3A or an institution notified under section 46 of the State Financial Corporations Act, 1951`
  line `(63 of 1951);`
  line `( c ) “State industrial investment corporation” means a Government company within the meaning`
  line `of section 617 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), engaged in the business of providing long-`
  line `term finance for industrial projects and 5 [eligible for deduction under clause ( viii ) of sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `ofsection 36].]`
  line `6 [( d ) “co - operative bank”, primary agricultural credit society” and “primary co -operative`
  line `agricultural and rural dev elopment bank” shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in the`
  line `Explanation to sub-section ( 4 ) of section 80P.]`
  line `7 [ 43C. Special provision for computation of cost of acquisition of certain assets. — ( 1 ) Where an`
  line `asset [not being an asset referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) of section 45] which becomes the property of an`
  line `amalgamated company under a scheme of amalgamation, is sold after the 29th day of February, 1988, by`
  line `the amalgamated company as stock-in-trade of the business carried on by it, the cost of acquisition of the`
  line `said asset to the amalgamated company in computing the profits and gains from the sale of such asset`
  line `shall be the cost of acquisition of the said asset to the amalgamating company, as increased by the cost, if`
  line `any, of any improvement made thereto, and the expenditure, if any, incurred, wholly and exclusively in`
  line `connection with such transfer by the amalgamating company.`
  line `( 2 ) Where an asset [not being an asset referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) of section 45] which becomes the`
  line `property of the assessee on the total or partial partition of a Hindu undivided family or under a gift or will`
  line `or an irrevocable trust, is sold after the 29th day of February, 1988, by the assessee as stock-in-trade of`
  line `the business carried on by him, the cost of acquisition of the said asset to the assessee in computing the`
  line `profits and gains from the sale of such asset shall be the cost of acquisition of the said asset to the`
  line `transferor or the donor, as the case may be, as increased by the cost, if any, of any improvement made`
  line `thereto, and the expenditure, if any, incurred, wholly and exclusively in connection with such transfer (by`
  line `way of effecting the partition, acceptance of the gift, obtaining probate in respect of the will or the`
  line `creation of the trust), including the payment of gift-tax, if any, incurred by the transferor or the donor, as`
  line `the case may be.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w. e. f. 1-4-1997).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
