obj_root_law_sections_245_content:
  string
  line 245
  line `1 [43CA. Special provision for full value of consideration for transfer of assets other than capital`
  line `assets in certain cases. — ( 1 ) Where the consideration received or accruing as a result of the transfer by`
  line `an assessee of an asset (other than a capital asset), being land or building or both, is less than the value`
  line `adopted or assessed or assessable by any authority of a State Government for the purpose of payment of`
  line `stamp duty in respect of such transfer, the value so adopted or assessed or assessable shall, for the`
  line `purposes of computing profits and gains from transfer of such asset, be deemed to be the full value of the`
  line `consideration received or accruing as a result of such transfer.`
  line `2 [Provided that where the value adopted or assessed or assessable by the authority for the purpose of`
  line `payment of stamp duty does not exceed one hundred and five per cent. of the consideration received or`
  line `accruing as a result of the transfer, the consideration so received or accruing as a result of the transfer`
  line `shall, for the purposes of computing profits and gains from transfer of such asset, be deemed to be the full`
  line `value of the consideration.]`
  line `( 2 ) The provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) and sub-section ( 3 ) of section 50C shall, so far as may be, apply`
  line `in relation to determination of the value adopted or assessed or assessable under sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 3 ) Where the date of agreement fixing the value of consideration for transfer of the asset and the date`
  line `of registration of such transfer of asset are not the same, the value referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) may be`
  line `taken as the value assessable by any authority of a State Government for the purpose of payment of stamp`
  line `duty in respect of such transfer on the date of the agreement.`
  line `( 4 ) The provisions of sub-section ( 3 ) shall apply only in a case where the amount of consideration or`
  line `a part thereof has been received 3 [by way of an account payee cheque or an account payee bank draft or`
  line `by use of electronic clearing system through a bank account] on or before the date of agreement for`
  line `transfer of the asset.]`
  line `4 [ 43CB. Computation of income from construction and service contracts. — ( 1 ) The profits and`
  line `gains arising from a construction contract or a contract for providing services shall be determined on the`
  line `basis of percentage of completion method in accordance with the income computation and disclosure`
  line `standards notified under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 145:`
  line `Provided that profits and gains arising from a contract for providing services, —`
  line `( i ) with duration of not more than ninety days shall be determined on the basis of project`
  line `completion method;`
  line `( ii ) involving indeterminate number of acts over a specific period of time shall be determined on`
  line `the basis of straight line method.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for “by any mode other than cash” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2019).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 15 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_245_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_246:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-246
  sectionNo (246)
  orderNo 246
  title `Page 246`
  content obj_root_law_sections_246_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_246_footnotes
  sourcePage 246
obj_root_law_sections_246_content:
  string
  line 246
  line `( 2 ) For the purposes of percentage of completion method, project completion method or straight line`
  line `method referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) —`
  line `( i ) the contract revenue shall include retention money;`
  line `( ii ) the contract costs shall not be reduced by any incidental income in the nature of interest,`
  line `dividends or capital gains.]`
  line `1 [43D. Special provision in case of income of public financial institutions, public companies,`
  line `etc. — Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any other provision of this Act, —`
  line `( a ) in the case of a public financial institution or a scheduled bank or 2 [a co-operative bank other`
  line `than a primary agricultural credit society or a primary co-operative agricultural and rural development`
  line `bank or] a State financial corporation or a State industrial investment corporation, the income by way`
  line `of interest in relation to such categories of bad or doubtful debts as may be prescribed having regard`
  line `to the guidelines issued by the Reserve Bank of India in relation to such debts;`
  line `( b ) in the case of a public company, the income by way of interest in relation to such categories`
  line `of bad or doubtful debts as may be prescribed having regard to the guidelines issued by the National`
  line `Housing Bank in relation to such debts,`
  line `shall be chargeable to tax in the previous year in which it is credited by the public financial institution or`
  line `the scheduled bank or 2 [a co-operative bank other than a primary agricultural credit society or a primary`
  line `co-operative agricultural and rural development bank or] the State financial corporation or the State`
  line `industrial investment corporation or the public company to its profit and loss account for that year or, as`
  line `the case may be, in which it is actually received by that institution or bank or corporation or company,`
  line `whichever is earlier.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “National Housing Bank” means the Nat ional Housing Bank established under section 3 of`
  line `the National Housing Bank Act, 1987 (53 of 1987);`
  line `( b ) “public company” means a company,—`
  line `( i ) which is a public company within the meaning of section 3 of the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line `( ii ) whose main object is carrying on the business of providing long-term finance for`
  line `construction or purchase of houses in India for residential purposes; and`
  line `( iii ) which is registered in accordance with the Housing Finance Companies`
  line `(NHB) Directions, 1989 given under section 30 and section 31 of the National Housing Bank`
  line `Act, 1987 (53 of 1987);`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 28, for Section 43D (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
