obj_root_law_sections_247_content:
  string
  line 247
  line `( c ) “public financial institution” shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 4A of the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line `( d ) “scheduled bank” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( ii ) of the Explanation to`
  line `clause ( viia ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 36;`
  line `( e ) “State financial corporation” means a financial corporation established under`
  line `section 3 or section 3A or an institution notified under section 46 of the State Financial Corporations`
  line `Act, 1951 (63 of 1951);`
  line `( f ) “State industrial investment corporation” means a Government company within the meaning`
  line `of section 617 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), engaged in the business of providing long-`
  line `term finance for industrial projects.]`
  line `1 [( g ) “co - operative bank”, “primary agricultural credit society” and “primary co -operative`
  line `agricultural and rural development bank” shall have the meanings respec tively assigned to them in the`
  line `Explanation to sub-section ( 4 ) of section 80P.]`
  line `44. Insurance business. — Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in the provisions of`
  line `this Act relating to the computation of income chargeable under the head “Interest on securities”,`
  line `“Income from house property”, “Capital gains” or “Income from other sources”, or in section 199 or in`
  line `2 [section 28 to 43B], the profits and gains of any business of insurance, including any such business`
  line `carried on by a mutual insurance company or by a co-operative society, shall be computed in accordance`
  line `with the rules contained in the First Schedule.`
  line `3 [ 44A. Special provision for deduction in the case of trade, professional or similar association. —`
  line `( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Act, where the amount received during a`
  line `previous year by any trade, professional or similar association (other than an association or institution`
  line `referred to in clause ( 23A ) of section 10) from its members, whether by way of subscription or otherwise`
  line `(not being remuneration received for rendering any specific services to such members) falls short of the`
  line `expenditure incurred by such association during that previous year (not being expenditure deductible in`
  line `computing the income under any other provision of this Act and not being in the nature of capital`
  line `expenditure) solely for the purposes of protection or advancement of the common interests of its`
  line `members, the amount so fallen short (hereinafter referred to as deficiency) shall, subject to the provisions`
  line `of this section, be allowed as a deduction in computing the income of the association assessable for the`
  line `relevant assessment year under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession” and if there is no`
  line `income assessable under that head or the deficiency allowable exceeds such income, the whole or the`
  line `balance of the deficiency, as the case may be, shall be allowed as a deduction in computing the income of`
  line `the association assessable for the relevant assessment year under any other head.`
  line `( 2 ) In computing the income of the association for the relevant assessment year under sub-section ( 1 ),`
  line `effect shall first be given to any other provision of this Act under which any allowance or loss in respect`
  line `of any earlier assessment year is carried forward and set off against the income for the relevant`
  line `assessment year.`
  line `( 3 ) The amount of deficiency to be allowed as a deduction under this section shall in no case exceed`
  line `one-half of the total income of the association as computed before making any allowance under this`
  line section.
  line `( 4 ) This section applies only to that trade, professional or similar association the income of which or`
  line `any part thereof is not distributed to its members except as grants to any association or institution`
  line `affiliated to it.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 126, for “section 28 to 43A” (w.e.f 1 -4-1989).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 5 of 1964, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1964).`
