obj_root_law_sections_248_content:
  string
  line 248
  line `1 [44AA. Maintenance of accounts by certain persons carrying on profession or business. — ( 1 )`
  line `Every person carrying on legal, medical, engineering or architectural profession or the profession of`
  line `accountancy or technical consultancy or interior decoration or any other profession as is notified by the`
  line `Board in the Official Gazette shall keep and maintain such books of account and other documents as may`
  line `enable the 2 [Assessing Officer] to compute his total income in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) Every person carrying on business or profession [not being a profession referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 )] shall, —`
  line `( i ) if his income from business or profession exceeds 3 [one lakh twenty thousand] rupees or his`
  line `total sales, turnover or gross receipts, as the case may be, in business or profession exceed or exceeds`
  line `4 [ten lakh] rupees in any one of the three years immediately preceding the previous year; or`
  line `( ii ) where the business or profession is newly set up in any previous year, if his income from`
  line `business or profession is likely to exceed 3 [one lakh twenty thousand] rupees or his total sales,`
  line `turnover or gross receipts, as the case may be, in business or profession are or is likely to exceed 4 [ten`
  line `lakh] rupees, 5 [during such previous year; or`
  line `( iii ) where the profits and gains from the business are deemed to be the profits and gains of the`
  line `assessee under 6 [section 44AE] 7 [or section 44BB or section 44BBB], as the case may be, and the`
  line `assessee has claimed his income to be lower than the profits or gains so deemed to be the profits and`
  line `gains of his business, as the case may be, during such 8 [previous year; or]]`
  line `9 [( iv ) where the provisions of sub-section ( 4 ) of section 44AD are applicable in his case and his`
  line `income exceeds the maximum amount which is not chargeable to income-tax in any previous year,]`
  line `keep and maintain such books of account and other documents as may enable the 2 [Assessing Officer] to`
  line `compute his total income in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
  line `10 [Provided that in the case of a person being an individual or a Hindu undivided family, the`
  line `provisions of clause ( i ) and clause ( ii ) shall have effect, as if for the words “one lakh twenty thousand`
  line `rupees”, the words “two lakh fifty thousand rupees” had been substituted:`
  line `Provided further that in the case of a person being an individual or a Hindu undivided family, the`
  line `provisions of clause ( i ) and clause ( ii ) shall have effect, as if for the words “ten lakh rupees”, the words`
  line `“twenty - five rupees” had been substituted.]`
  line `( 3 ) The Board may, having regard to the nature of the business or profession carried on by any class`
  line `of persons, prescribe, by rules, the books of account and other documents (including inventories,`
  line `wherever necessary) to be kept and maintained under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ), the particulars to`
  line `be contained therein and the form and the manner in which and the place at which they shall be kept and`
  line maintained.
  line `( 4 ) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section ( 3 ), the Board may prescribe, by rules, the`
  line `period for which the books of account and other documents to be kept and maintained under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) shall be retained.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for Income- tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 20, for “forty thousand” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1999).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 20, ibid., for “five hundred thousand” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1999).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 10, for “during such previous year” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1998).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 18, for “section 44AD or section 44AE or section 44AF” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2011).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009. S. 18, for “previous year” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2011).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 24, for clause ( iv ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
