obj_root_law_sections_250_content:
  string
  line 250
  line `1 [Provided also] that] in a case where such person is required by or under any other law to get his`
  line `accounts audited 2 ***, it shall be sufficient compliance with the provisions of this section if such person`
  line `gets the accounts of such business or profession audited under such law before the specified date and`
  line `3 [furnishes by] that date the report of the audit as required under such other law and a further report 4 [by`
  line `an accountant] in the form prescribed under this section.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “accountant” shall have the same meaning as in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 288;`
  line `5 [( ii ) “specified date”, in relation to the accounts of the assessee of the previous year relevant to`
  line `an assessment year, means 6 [the due date for furnishing the return of income under sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 139].]]`
  line `44AC. [ Special provision for computing profits and gains from the business of trading in`
  line `certain goods. ] Omitted by the Finance Act, 1992 (18 of 1992), s. 21 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `7 [ 44AD. Special provision for computing profits and gains of business on presumptive`
  line `basis. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in sections 28 to 43C,in the case of an`
  line `eligible assessee engaged in an eligible business, a sum equal to eight per cent of the total turnover or`
  line `gross receipts of the assessee in the previous year on account of such business or, as the case may be, a`
  line `sum higher than the aforesaid sum claimed to have been earned by the eligible assessee, shall be deemed`
  line `to be the profits and gains of such business chargeable to tax under the head “Profits and gains of bu siness`
  line `or profession”.`
  line `8 [Provided that this sub- section shall have effect as if for the words “eight per cent.”, the words “six`
  line `per cent.” had been substituted, in respect of the amount of total turnover or gross receipts which is`
  line `received by an account payee cheque or an account payee bank draft or use of electronic clearing system`
  line `through a bank account during the previous year or before the due date specified in sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 139 in respect of that previous year.]`
  line `( 2 ) Any deduction allowable under the provisions of sections 30 to 38 shall, for the purposes of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ), be deemed to have been already given full effect to and no further deduction under those`
  line `sections shall be allowed:`
  line `9 * * * * *`
  line `( 3 ) The written down value of any asset of an eligible business shall be deemed to have been`
  line `calculated as if the eligible assessee had claimed and had been actually allowed the deduction in respect`
  line `of the depreciation for each of the relevant assessment years.`
  line `10 [( 4 ) Where an eligible assessee declares profit for any previous year in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this section and he declares profit for any of the five assessment years relevant to the`
  line `previous year succeeding such previous year not in accordance with the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ), he`
  line `shall not be eligible to claim the benefit of the provisions of this section for five assessment years`
  line `subsequent to the assessment year relevant to the previous year in which the profit has not been declared`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 20, for “Provided further” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `2. The words “by an accountant” omitted by Act 32 of 1985, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1985).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 13, for “obtains before” (w.e.f. 1 -7-1995).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 28, ibid., for clause ( ii ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 13, for “the 30th day of September of the assessment year” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2012).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 20, for section 44AD (w.e.f. 1-4-2011).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `9. The proviso omitted by Act 28 of 2016, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `10. Subs. by s. 26, ibid., for sub-sections ( 4 ) and ( 5 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
