obj_root_law_sections_251_content:
  string
  line 251
  line `( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, an eligible`
  line `assessee to whom the provisions of sub-section ( 4 ) are applicable and whose total income exceeds the`
  line `maximum amount which is not chargeable to income-tax, shall be required to keep and maintain such`
  line `books of account and other documents as required under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 44AA and get them`
  line `audited and furnish a report of such audit as required under section 44AB.]`
  line `1 [( 6 ) The provisions of this section, notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions,`
  line `shall not apply to —`
  line `( i ) a person carrying on profession as referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 44AA;`
  line `( ii ) a person earning income in the nature of commission or brokerage; or`
  line `( iii ) a person carrying on any agency business.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “eligibleassessee” means,—`
  line `( i ) an individual, Hindu undivided family or a partnership firm, who is a resident, but not a`
  line `limited liability partnership firm as defined under clause ( n ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 2 of the`
  line `Limited Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009); and`
  line `( ii ) who has not claimed deduction under any of the sections 10A, 10AA, 10B, 10BAor`
  line `deduction under any provisions of Chapter VIA under the heading ”C. - Deductions in respect of`
  line `certain incomes” in the relevant assessment year;`
  line `( b ) “eligible business” means,—`
  line `( i ) any business except the business of plying, hiring or leasing goods carriages referred to in`
  line `section 44AE; and`
  line `( ii ) whose total turnover or gross receipts in the previous year does not exceed an amount of`
  line `2 [two crore rupees].]`
  line `3 [44ADA. Special provision for computing profits and gains of profession on presumptive`
  line `basis. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sections 28 to 43C, in the case of an assessee, being a`
  line `resident in India, who is engaged in a profession referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 44AAand whose`
  line `total gross receipts do not exceed fifty lakh rupees in a previous year, a sum equal to fifty per cent. of the`
  line `total gross receipts of the assessee in the previous year on account of such profession or, as the case may`
  line `be, a sum higher than the aforesaid sum claimed to have been earned by the assessee, shall be deemed to`
  line `be the profits and gains of such profession chargeable to tax under the head “Profits and gains of business`
  line `or profession”.`
  line `( 2 ) Any deduction allowable under the provisions of sections 30 to 38shall, for the purposes of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ), be deemed to have been already given full effect to and no further deduction under those`
  line `sections shall be allowed.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-2011).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 26, for “one crore rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 27, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_251_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_252:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-252
