obj_root_law_sections_252_content:
  string
  line 252
  line `( 3 ) The written down value of any asset used for the purposes of profession shall be deemed to have`
  line `been calculated as if the assessee had claimed and had been actually allowed the deduction in respect of`
  line `the depreciation for each of the relevant assessment years.`
  line `( 4 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, an assessee who`
  line `claims that his profits and gains from the profession are lower than the profits and gains specified in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) and whose total income exceeds the maximum amount which is not chargeable to`
  line `income-tax, shall be required to keep and maintain such books of account and other documents as`
  line `required under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 44AA and get them audited and furnish a report of such audit as`
  line `required under section 44AB.]`
  line `1 [44AE. Special provision for computing profits and gains of business of plying, hiring or`
  line `leasing goods carriages. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in sections 28 to 43A,`
  line `in the case of an assessee, who owns not more than ten goods carriages 2 [at any time during the previous`
  line `year] and who is engaged in the business of plying, hiring or leasing such goods carriages, the income of`
  line `such business chargeable to tax under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession” shall be`
  line `deemed to be the aggregate of the profits and gains, from all the goods carriages owned by him in the`
  line `previous year, computed in accordance with the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ).`
  line `3 [( 2 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), the profits and gains from each goods carriage, —`
  line `( i ) being a heavy goods vehicle, shall be an amount equal to one thousand rupees per ton of gross`
  line `vehicle weight or unladen weight, as the case may be, for every month or part of a month during`
  line `which the heavy goods vehicle is owned by the assessee in the previous year or an amount claimed to`
  line `have been actually earned from such vehicle, whichever is higher;`
  line `( ii ) other than heavy goods vehicle, shall be an amount equal to seven thousand five hundred`
  line `rupees for every month or part of a month during which the goods carriage is owned by the assessee`
  line `in the previous year or an amount claimed to have been actually earned from such goods carriage,`
  line `whichever is higher.]`
  line `( 3 ) Any deduction allowable under the provisions of sections 30 to 38shall, for the purposes of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ), be deemed to have been already given full effect to and no further deduction under those`
  line `sections shall be allowed:`
  line `4 [Provided that where the assessee is a firm, the salary and interest paid to its partners shall be`
  line `deducted from the income computed under sub-section ( 1 ) subject to the conditions and limits specified in`
  line `clause ( b ) of section 40.]`
  line `( 4 ) The written down value of any asset used for the purpose of the business referred to in sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) shall be deemed to have been calculated as if the assessee had claimed and had been actually allowed`
  line `the deduction in respect of the depreciation for each of the relevant assessment years.`
  line `( 5 ) The provisions of sections 44AA and 44ABshall not apply in so far as they relate to the business`
  line `referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) and in computing the monetary limits under those sections, the gross receipts`
  line `or, as the case may be, the income from the said business shall be excluded.`
  line `5 [( 6 ) Nothing contained in the foregoing provisions of this section shall apply, where the assessee`
  line `claims and produces evidence to prove that the profits and gains from the aforesaid business during the`
  line `previous year relevant to the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1997 or any earlier`
  line `assessment year, are lower than the profits and gains specified in sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ), and thereupon`
  line `the Assessing Officer shall proceed to make an assessment of the total income or loss of the assessee and`
  line `determine the sum payable by the assessee on the basis of assessment made under sub-section ( 3 ) of`
  line `section 143.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-1994).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 16, for sub-section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2019). Earlier it was substituted by Act 25 of 2014, s. 16`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-1994).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 11 of 1999, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-1997).`
