obj_root_law_sections_253_content:
  string
  line 253
  line `1 [( 7 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, an assessee may`
  line `claim lower profits and gains than the profits and gains specified in sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ), if he keeps`
  line `and maintains such books of account and other documents as required under sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 44AA and gets his accounts audited and furnishes a report of such audit as required under`
  line `section 44AB.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `2 [( a ) the expressions “goods carriage”, “gross vehicle weight” and “unladen weight” shall have`
  line `the respective meanings assigned to them in section 2 of the Motor Vehicles Act, 1988;`
  line `( aa ) the expression “heavy goods vehicle” means any goods carriage, the gross vehicle weight of`
  line `which exceeds 12000 kilograms;’ ]`
  line `( b ) anassessee, who is in possession of a goods carriage, whether taken on hire purchase or on`
  line `instalments and for which the whole or part of the amount payable is still due, shall be deemed to be`
  line `the owner of such goods carriage.]`
  line `3 [44AF. Special provisions for computing profits and gains of retail business. — ( 1 )`
  line `Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in sections 28 to 43C,in the case of an assessee`
  line `engaged in retail trade in any goods or merchandise, a sum equal to five per cent of the total turnover in`
  line `the previous year on account of such business or, as the case may be, a sum higher than the aforesaid sum`
  line `as declared by the assessee in his return of income shall be deemed to be the profits and gains of such`
  line `business chargeable to tax under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession”:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply in respect of an assessee whose total`
  line `turnover exceeds an amount of forty lakh rupees in the previous year.`
  line `( 2 ) Any deduction allowable under the provisions of sections 30 to 38 shall, for the purposes of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ), be deemed to have been already given full effect to and no further deduction under those`
  line `sections shall be allowed:`
  line `Provided that where the assessee is a firm, the salary and interest paid to its partners shall be deducted`
  line `from the income computed under sub-section ( 1 ) subject to the conditions and limits specified in`
  line `clause ( b ) of section 40.`
  line `( 3 ) The written down value of any asset used for the purpose of the business referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to have been calculated as if the assessee had claimed and had been`
  line `actually allowed the deduction in respect of the depreciation for each of the relevant assessment years.`
  line `( 4 ) The provisions of sections 44AA and 44AB shall not apply in so far as they relate to the business`
  line `referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) and in computing the monetary limits under those sections, the total turnover`
  line `or, as the case may be, the income from the said business shall be excluded.]`
  line `4 [( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, an assessee may`
  line `claim lower profits and gains than the profits and gains specified in sub-section ( 1 ), if he keeps and`
  line `maintains such books of account and other documents as required under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 44AA`
  line `and gets his accounts audited and furnishes a report of such audit as required under section 44AB.]`
  line `5 [( 6 ) Nothing contained in this section shall apply to any assessment year beginning on or after the 1st`
  line `day of April, 2011.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 16, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2019) which was earlier substituted by Act 25 of 2014, s. 16`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
