obj_root_law_sections_254_content:
  string
  line 254
  line `1 [44B. Special provision for computing profits and gains of shipping business in the case of`
  line `non-residents. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in sections 28 to 43A, in the`
  line `case of an assessee, being a non-resident, engaged in the business of operation of ships, a sum equal to`
  line `seven and a half per cent of the aggregate of the amounts specified in sub-section ( 2 ) shall be deemed to`
  line `be th e profits and gains of such business chargeable to tax under the head “Profits and gains of business`
  line `or profession”.`
  line `( 2 ) The amounts referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be the following, namely: —`
  line `( i ) the amount paid or payable (whether in or out of India) to the assessee or to any person on his`
  line `behalf on account of the carriage of passengers, livestock, mail or goods shipped at any port in India;`
  line and
  line `( ii ) the amount received or deemed to be received in India by or on behalf of the assessee on`
  line `account of the carriage of passengers, livestock, mail or goods shipped at any port outside India.]`
  line `2 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, the amount referred to in clause ( i ) or clause ( ii )`
  line `shall include the amount paid or payable or received or deemed to be received, as the case may be, by`
  line `way of demurrage charges or handling charges or any other amount of similar nature.]`
  line `3 [ 44BB. Special provision for computing profits and gains in connection with the business of`
  line `exploration, etc., of mineral oils. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in sections 28`
  line `to 41 and sections 43 and 43A, 4 [in the case of an assessee, being a non-resident,] engaged in the business`
  line `of providing services or facilities in connection with, or supplying plant and machinery on hire used, or to`
  line `be used, in the prospecting for, or extraction or production of, mineral oils, a sum equal to ten per cent of`
  line `the aggregate of the amounts specified in sub-section ( 2 ) shall be deemed to be the profits and gains of`
  line `such busine ss chargeable to tax under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession”:`
  line `Provided that this sub-section shall not apply in a case where the provisions of section 42 or`
  line `section 44D or 5 [section 44DA or] section 115A or section 293A apply for the purposes of computing`
  line `profits or gains or any other income referred to in those sections.`
  line `( 2 ) The amounts referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be the following, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the amount paid or payable (whether in or out of India) to the assessee or to any person on his`
  line `behalf on account of the provision of services and facilities in connection with, or supply of plant and`
  line `machinery on hire used, or to be used, in the prospecting for, or extraction or production of, mineral`
  line `oils in India; and`
  line `( b ) the amount received or deemed to be received in India by or on behalf of the assessee on`
  line `account of the provision of services and facilities in connection with, or supply of plant and`
  line `machinery on hire used, or to be used, in the prospecting for, or extraction or production of, mineral`
  line `oils outside India.`
  line `6 [( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), an assessee may claim lower profits and`
  line `gains than the profits and gains specified in that sub-section, if he keeps and maintains such books of`
  line `account and other documents as required under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 44AA and gets his accounts`
  line `audited and furnishes a report of such audit as required under section 44AB, and thereupon the Assessing`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 1975, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1983).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 16, for “in the case of an assessee” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1983).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-2011).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
