obj_root_law_sections_255_content:
  string
  line 255
  line `Officer shall proceed to make an assessment of the total income or loss of the assessee under`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ) of section 143 and determine the sum payable by, or refundable to, the assessee.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “plant” includes ships, aircraft, vehicles, drilling units, scientific apparatus and equipment,`
  line `used for the purposes of the said business;`
  line `( ii ) “mineral oil” includes petroleum and natural gas.]`
  line `1 [44BBA. Special provision for computing profits and gains of the business of operation of`
  line `aircraft in the case of non-residents. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained`
  line `in sections 28 to 43A, in the case of an assessee, being a non-resident, engaged in the business of`
  line `operation of aircraft, a sum equal to five per cent. of the aggregate of the amounts specified in`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) shall be deemed to be the profits and gains of such business chargeable to tax under the`
  line `head “Profits and gains of business or profession”.`
  line `( 2 ) The amounts referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be the following, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the amount paid or payable (whether in or out of India) to the assessee or to any person on his`
  line `behalf on account of the carriage of passengers, livestock, mail or goods from any place in India; and`
  line `( b ) the amount received or deemed to be received in India by or on behalf of the assessee on`
  line `account of the carriage of passengers, livestock, mail or goods from any place outside India.]`
  line `2 [ 44BBB. Special provision for computing profits and gains of foreign companies engaged in the`
  line `business of civil construction, etc., in certain turnkey power projects. — 3 [( 1 )] Notwithstanding`
  line `anything to the contrary contained insections 28 to 44AA, in the case of an assessee, being a foreign`
  line `company, engaged in the business of civil construction or the business of erection of plant or machinery`
  line `or testing or commissioning thereof, in connection with a turnkey power project approved by the Central`
  line `Government in this behalf 4 ***, a sum equal to ten per cent. of the amount paid or payable (whether in or`
  line `out of India) to the said assessee or to any person on his behalf on account of such civil construction,`
  line `erection, testing or commissioning shall be deemed to be the profits and gains of such business chargeable`
  line `to tax under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession”.]`
  line `5 [( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), an assessee may claim lower profits and`
  line `gains than the profits and gains specified in that sub-section, if he keeps and maintains such books of`
  line `account and other documents as required under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 44AA and gets his accounts`
  line `audited and furnishes a report of such audit as required under section 44AB, and thereupon the Assessing`
  line `Officer shall proceed to make an assessment of the total income or loss of the assessee under`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ) of section 143 and determine the sum payable by, or refundable to, the assessee.]`
  line `6 [44C. Deduction of head office expenditure in the case of non-residents. — Notwithstanding`
  line `anything to the contrary contained in sections 28 to 43A, in the case of an assessee, being a non-resident,`
  line `no allowance shall be made, in computing the income chargeable under the head “Profits and gains of`
  line `business or profession”, in respect of so much of the expenditure in the nature of head office expenditure`
  line `as is in excess of the amount computed as hereunder, namely: —`
  line `( a ) an amount equal to five per cent of the adjusted total income; or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 1989, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `3. The existing section numbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 32 of 2003, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `4. The words “and financed under any international aid programme” omitted by s. 26, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 26, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 66 of 1976, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-6-1976).`
