obj_root_law_sections_256_content:
  string
  line 256
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `( c ) the amount of so much of the expenditure in the nature of head office expenditure incurred by`
  line `the assessee as is attributable to the business or profession of the assessee in India,`
  line `whichever is the least:`
  line `Provided that in a case where the adjusted total income of the assessee is a loss, the amount under`
  line `clause ( a ) shall be computed at the rate of five per cent.of the average adjusted total income of the`
  line assessee.
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “adjusted total income” means the total income computed in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of this Act, without giving effect to the allowance referred to in this section or in sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 32or the deduction referred to in section 32Aor section 33or section 33A or the first proviso to`
  line `clause ( ix ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 36 or any loss carried forward under sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 72 or sub-section ( 2 ) of section 73 or 2 [sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 3 ) of section 74] or`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ) of section 74A or the deductions under Chapter VI-A;`
  line `( ii ) “average adjusted total income” means,—`
  line `( a ) in a case where the total income of the assessee is assessable for each of the three`
  line `assessment years immediately preceding the relevant assessment year, one-third of the aggregate`
  line `amount of the adjusted total income in respect of the previous years relevant to the aforesaid three`
  line `assessment years;`
  line `( b ) in a case where the total income of the assessee is assessable only for two of the aforesaid`
  line `three assessment years, one-half of the aggregate amount of the adjusted total income in respect`
  line `of the previous years relevant to the aforesaid two assessment years;`
  line `( c ) in a case where the total income of the assessee is assessable only for one of the aforesaid`
  line `three assessment years, the amount of the adjusted total income in respect of the previous year`
  line `relevant to that assessment year;`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `( iv ) “head office expenditure” means executive and general administration expenditure incurred`
  line `by the assessee outside India, including expenditure incurred in respect of —`
  line `( a ) rent, rates, taxes, repairs or insurance of any premises outside India used for the purposes`
  line `of the business or profession;`
  line `( b ) salary, wages, annuity, pension, fees, bonus, commission, gratuity, perquisites or profits`
  line `in lieu of or in addition to salary, whether paid or allowed to any employee or other person`
  line `employed in, or managing the affairs of, any office outside India;`
  line `( c ) travelling by any employee or other person employed in, or managing the affairs of, any`
  line `office outside India; and`
  line `( d ) such other matters connected with executive and general administration as may be`
  line prescribed.]
  line `1. Clause ( b ) omitted by Act 38 of 1993, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 74, for “sub -section ( 1 ) of section 74” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Clause ( iii ) omitted by Act 38 of 1993, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
