obj_root_law_sections_257_content:
  string
  line 257
  line `1 [44D. Special provisions for computing income by way of royalties, etc., in the case of foreign`
  line `companies. — Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in sections 28 to 44C, in the case of an`
  line `assessee, being a foreign company, —`
  line `( a ) the deductions admissible under the said sections in computing the income by way of royalty`
  line `or fees for technical services received 2 [from Government or an Indian concern in pursuance of an`
  line `agreement made by the foreign company with Government or with the Indian concern] before the 1st`
  line `day of April, 1976, shall not exceed in the aggregate twenty per cent of the gross amount of such`
  line `royalty or fees as reduced by so much of the gross amount of such royalty as consists of lump sum`
  line `consideration for the transfer outside India of, or the imparting of information outside India in respect`
  line `of, any data, documentation, drawing or specification relating to any patent, invention, model, design,`
  line `secret formula or process or trade mark or similar property;`
  line `( b ) no deduction in respect of any expenditure or allowance shall be allowed under any of the said`
  line `sections in computing the income by way of royalty or fees for technical services received [from`
  line `Government or an Indian concern in pursuance of an agreement made by the foreign company with`
  line `Government or with the Indian concern] after the 31st day of March, 1976 3 [but before the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2003;]`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “fees for technical services” shall have the same meaning as in 5 [ Explanation 2 to clause ( vii )`
  line `of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 9];`
  line `( b ) “foreign company” shall have the same meaning as in section 80B;`
  line `( c ) “royalty” shall have the same meaning as in 6 [ Explanation 2 to clause ( vi ) of sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 9];`
  line `( d ) royalty received 2 [from Government or an Indian concern in pursuance of an agreement made`
  line `by a foreign company with Government or with the Indian concern] after the 31st day of March,`
  line `1976, shall be deemed to have been received in pursuance of an agreement made before the 1st day of`
  line `April, 1976, if such agreement is deemed, for the purposes of the proviso to clause ( vi ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 9, to have been made before the 1st day of April, 1976.]`
  line `7 [44DA. Special provision for computing income by way of royalties, etc., in case of non-`
  line `residents. — ( 1 ) The income by way of royalty or fees for technical services received from Government`
  line `or an Indian concern in pursuance of an agreement made by a non-resident (not being a company) or a`
  line `foreign company with Government or the Indian concern after the 31st day of March, 2003, where such`
  line `non-resident (not being a company) or a foreign company carries on business in India through a`
  line `permanent establishment situated therein, or performs professional services from a fixed place of`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 66 of 1976, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-6-1976).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 11 of 1983, s. 19, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-6-1983).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `4. Clause ( c ) and ( d ) omitted by Act 32 of 1994, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 29, for “the Explanation to, clause ( vii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 9” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1977).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 29, ibid., for “the Explanation to clause ( vi ) of sub- section ( 1 ) of section 9” (w.e.f 1 -4-1977).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 28 (w.e.f 1-4-2004).`
