obj_root_law_sections_258_content:
  string
  line 258
  line `profession situated therein, and the right, property or contract in respect of which the royalties or fees for`
  line `technical services are paid is effectively connected with such permanent establishment or fixed place of`
  line `profession, as the case may be, shall be computed under the head “Profits and gains of business or`
  line `profession” in accordance with the provisions of this Act:`
  line `Provided that no deduction shall be allowed, —`
  line `( i ) in respect of any expenditure or allowance which is not wholly and exclusively incurred for`
  line `the business of such permanent establishment or fixed place of profession in India; or`
  line `( ii ) in respect of amounts, if any, paid (otherwise than towards reimbursement of actual expenses)`
  line `by the permanent establishment to its head office or to any of its other offices:`
  line `1 [Provided further that the provisions of section 44BB shall not apply in respect of the income`
  line `referred to in this section.]`
  line `( 2 ) Every non-resident (not being a company) or a foreign company shall keep and maintain books of`
  line `account and other documents in accordance with the provisions contained in section 44AA and get his`
  line `accounts audited by an accountant as defined in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288 and`
  line `furnish along with the return of income, the report of such audit in the prescribed form duly signed and`
  line `verified by such accountant.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “fees for technical services” shall have the same meaning as in Explanation 2 to clause ( vii ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 9;`
  line `( b ) “royalty” shall have the same meaning as in Explanation 2 to clause ( vi ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 9;`
  line `( c ) “permanent establishment” shall have the same meaning as in clau se ( iiia ) of section 92F.]`
  line `2 [44DB. Special provision for computing deductions in the case of business reorganization of co-`
  line `operative banks. — ( 1 ) The deduction under section 32, section 35D, section 35DD or`
  line `section 35DDA shall, in a case where business reorganisation of a co-operative bank has taken place`
  line `during the financial year, be allowed in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line `( 2 ) The amount of deduction allowable to the predecessor co-operative bank under section 32,`
  line `section 35D, section 35DD or section DDA shall be determined in accordance with the formula —`
  line `A X B`
  line C
  line `where A = the amount of deduction allowable to the predecessor co-operative bank if the business`
  line `reorganisation had not taken place;`
  line `B = the number of days comprised in the period beginning with the 1st day of the financial`
  line `year and ending on the day immediately preceding the date of business reorganisation; and`
  line `C = the total number of days in the financial year in which the business reorganisation has`
  line `taken place.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2011).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_258_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_259:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-259
  sectionNo (259)
  orderNo 259
  title `Page 259`
  content obj_root_law_sections_259_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_259_footnotes
  sourcePage 259
obj_root_law_sections_259_content:
  string
  line 259
  line `(3) The amount of deduction allowable to the successor co-operative bank under section 32,`
  line `section 35D, section 35DD or section 35DDA shall be determined in accordance with the formula —`
  line `A X B`
  line C
  line `where A = the amount of deduction allowable to the predecessor co-operative bank if the business`
  line `reorganisation had not taken place;`
  line `B = the number of days comprised in the period beginning with the date of business reorganisation`
  line `and ending on the last day of the financial year; and`
  line `C = the total number of days in the financial year in which the business reorganisation has taken`
  line place.
  line `( 4 ) The provisions of section 35D, section 35DD or section 35DDA shall, in a case where an`
  line `undertaking of the predecessor co-operative bank entitled to the deduction under the said section is`
  line `transferred before the expiry of the period specified therein to a successor co-operative bank on account`
  line `of business reorganisation, apply to the successor co-operative bank in the financial years subsequent to`
  line `the year of business reorganisation as they would have applied to the predecessor co-operative bank, as if`
  line `the business reorganisation had not taken place.`
  line `( 5 ) For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “amalgamated co - operative bank” means —`
  line `( i ) a co-operative bank with which one or more amalgamating co-operative banks merge; or`
  line `( ii ) a co-operative bank formed as a result of merger of two or more amalgamating`
  line `co-operative banks;`
  line `( b ) “amalgamating co - operative bank” means—`
  line `( i ) a co-operative bank which merges with another co-operative bank; or`
  line `( ii ) every co-operative bank merging to form a new co-operative bank;`
  line `( c ) “amalgamation” means the merger of an amalgamating co -operative bank or banks with an`
  line `amalgamated co-operative bank, in such manner that —`
  line `( i ) all the assets and liabilities of the amalgamating co-operative bank or banks immediately`
  line `before the merger (other than the assets transferred, by sale or distribution on winding up, to the`
  line `amalgamated co-operative bank) become the assets and liabilities of the amalgamated`
  line `co-operative bank;`
  line `( ii ) the members holding seventy-five per cent or more voting rights in the amalgamating`
  line `co-operative bank become members of the amalgamated co-operative bank; and`
obj_root_law_sections_259_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_260:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-260
  sectionNo (260)
  orderNo 260
  title `Page 260`
  content obj_root_law_sections_260_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_260_footnotes
  sourcePage 260
obj_root_law_sections_260_content:
  string
  line 260
  line `( iii ) the shareholders holding seventy-five per cent or more in value of the shares in the`
  line `amalgamating co-operative bank (other than the shares held by the amalgamated co-operative`
  line `bank or its nominee or its subsidiary, immediately before the merger) become shareholders of the`
  line `amalgamated co-operative bank;`
  line `( d ) “business reorganisation” means the reorganisation of business involving the amalgamation or`
  line `demerger of a co-operative bank;`
  line `( e ) ”co - operative bank” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clau se ( cci ) of section 5 of the`
  line `Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949);`
  line `( f ) “demerger” means the transfer by a demerged co -operative bank of one or more of its`
  line `undertakings to any resulting co-operative bank, in such manner that —`
  line `( i ) all the assets and liabilities of the undertaking or undertakings immediately before the`
  line `transfer become the assets and liabilities of the resulting co-operative bank;`
  line `( ii ) the assets and the liabilities are transferred to the resulting co-operative bank at values`
  line `(other than change in the value of assets consequent to their revaluation) appearing in its books of`
  line `account immediately before the transfer;`
  line `( iii ) the resulting co-operative bank issues, in consideration of the transfer, its membership to`
  line `the members of the demerged co-operative bank on a proportionate basis;`
  line `( iv ) the shareholders holding seventy-five per cent or more in value of the shares in the`
  line `demerged co-operative bank (other than shares already held by the resulting bank or its nominee`
  line `or its subsidiary immediately before the transfer), become shareholders of the resulting co-`
  line `operative bank, otherwise than as a result of the acquisition of the assets of the demerged co-`
  line `operative bank or any undertaking thereof by the resulting co-operative bank;`
  line `( v ) the transfer of the undertaking is on a going concern basis; and`
  line `( vi ) the transfer is in accordance with the conditions specified by the Central Government, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, having regard to the necessity to ensure that the transfer is for`
  line `genuine business purposes;`
  line `( g ) “demerged co - operative bank” means the co -operative bank whose undertaking is transferred,`
  line `pursuant to a demerger, to a resulting bank;`
  line `( h ) “predecessor co - operative bank” means the amalgamating co -operative bank or the demerged`
  line `co-operative bank, as the case may be;`
  line `( i ) “successor co - operative bank” means the amalgamated co -operative bank or the resulting`
  line `bank, as the case may be;`
  line `( j ) “resulting co - operative bank” means—`
  line `( i ) one or more co-operative banks to which the undertaking of the demerged co-operative`
  line `bank is transferred in a demerger; or`
  line `( ii ) any co-operative bank formed as a result of demerger.]`
