obj_root_law_sections_261_content:
  string
  line 261
  line `E. — Capital gains`
  line `45. Capital gains. — 1 [( 1 )] Any profits or gains arising from the transfer of a capital asset effected in`
  line `previous year shall, save as otherwise provided in 2 [sections 3 *** 54, 4 *** 5 [54B, 6 [54D, 7 [54E, 8 [54EA,`
  line `54EB,] 54F, 9 [54G and 54H]]]]], be chargeable to income- tax under the head “Capital gains”, and shall be`
  line `deemed to be the income of the previous year in which the transfer took place.`
  line `10 [( 1A ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), where any person receives at any time`
  line `during any previous year any money or other assets under an insurance from an insurer on account of`
  line `damage to, or destruction of, any capital asset, as a result of —`
  line `( i ) flood, typhoon, hurricane, cyclone, earthquake or other convulsion of nature; or`
  line `( ii ) riot or civil disturbance; or`
  line `( iii ) accidental fire or explosion; or`
  line `( iv ) action by an enemy or action taken in combating an enemy (whether with or without a`
  line `declaration of war),`
  line `then, any profits or gains arising from receipt of such money or other assets shall be chargeable to`
  line `income- tax under the head “Capital gains” and shall be deemed to be the income of such person of the`
  line `previous year in which such money or other asset was received and for the purposes of section 48, value`
  line `of any money or the fair market value of other assets on the date of such receipt shall be deemed to be the`
  line `full value of the consideration received or accruing as a result of the transfer of such capital asset.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- section, the expression “insurer” shall have the meaning`
  line `assigned to it in clause ( 9 ) of section 2 of the Insurance Act, 1938 (4 of 1938).]`
  line `11 [( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), the profits or gains arising from the`
  line `transfer by way of conversion by the owner of a capital asset into, or its treatment by him as stock-in-`
  line `trade of a business carried on by him shall be chargeable to income-tax as his income of the previous year`
  line `in which such stock-in-trade is sold or otherwise transferred by him and, for the purposes of section 48,`
  line `the fair market value of the asset on the date of such conversion or treatment shall be deemed to be the`
  line `full value of the consideration received or accruing as a result of the transfer of the capital asset.]`
  line `12 [( 2A ) Where any person has had at any time during previous year any beneficial interest in any`
  line `securities, then, any profits or gains arising from transfer made by the depository or participant of such`
  line `beneficial interest in respect of securities shall be chargeable to income-tax as the income of the`
  line `beneficial owner of the previous year in which such transfer took place and shall not be regarded as`
  line `1. Sub-section ( I ) renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 5 of 1964, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-1964).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 19 of 1970, s. 11, for “sections 53 and 54” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1970).`
  line `3. The figures “53,” omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `4. The figures and letter “54C” omitted by Act 66 of 1976, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1976).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 29, for “54B and 54D” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1978).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 14 of 1982, s. 32 for “54D and 54E” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1983)`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 1 1 of 1987, s. 13, for “54E and 54F (w.e.f. 1 -10-1987).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 19, for “54E” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1996).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 17, for “and 54G” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1991).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `11. Ins. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `12. Ins. by Act 22 of 1996, s. 30 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 20-9-1995).`
