obj_root_law_sections_262_content:
  string
  line 262
  line `income of the depository who is deemed to be the registered owner of securities by virtue of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 10 of the Depositories Act, 1996, and for the purposes of —`
  line `( i ) section 48; and`
  line `( ii ) proviso to clause ( 42A ) of section 2,`
  line `the cost of acquisition and the period of holding of any securities shall be determined on the basis of the`
  line `first-in-first-out method.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- section, the expressions “beneficial owner”, “depository”`
  line `and “security” shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in clauses ( a ), ( e ) and ( l ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 2 of the Depositories Act, 1996.]`
  line `1 [( 3 ) The profits or gains arising from the transfer of a capital asset by a person to a firm or other`
  line `association of persons or body of individuals (not being a company or a co-operative society) in which he`
  line `is or becomes a partner or member, by way of capital contribution or otherwise, shall be chargeable to tax`
  line `as his income of the previous year in which such transfer takes place and, for the purposes of section 48,`
  line `the amount recorded in the books of account of the firm, association or body as the value of the capital`
  line `asset shall be deemed to be the full value of the consideration received or accruing as a result of the`
  line `transfer of the capital asset.`
  line `( 4 ) The profits or gains arising from the transfer of a capital asset by way of distribution of capital`
  line `assets on the dissolution of a firm or other association of persons or body of individuals (not being a`
  line `company or a co-operative society) or otherwise, shall be chargeable to tax as the income of the firm,`
  line `association or body, of the previous year in which the said transfer takes place and, for the purposes of`
  line `section 48, the fair market value of the asset on the date of such transfer shall be deemed to be the full`
  line `value of the consideration received or accruing as a result of the transfer.]`
  line `( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), where the capital gain arises from the`
  line `transfer of a capital asset, being a transfer by way of compulsory acquisition under any law, or a transfer`
  line `the consideration for which was determined or approved by the Central Government or the Reserve Bank`
  line `of India, and the compensation or the consideration for such transfer is enhanced or further enhanced by`
  line `any court, Tribunal or other authority, the capital gain shall be dealt with in the following manner,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( a ) the capital gain computed with reference to the compensation awarded in the first instance or,`
  line `as the case may be, the consideration determined or approved in the first instance by the Central`
  line `Government or the Reserve Bank of India shall be chargeable as 2 [income under the head “Capital`
  line `gains” of the previous year in which such compensation or part thereof, or such consideration or part`
  line `thereof, was first received]; and`
  line `( b ) the amount by which the compensation or consideration is enhanced or further enhanced by`
  line `the court, Tribunal or other authority shall be deemed to be income chargeable under the head`
  line `“Capital gains” of the previous year in which such amount is received by the assessee:`
  line `3 [Provided that any amount of compensation received in pursuance of an interim order of a court,`
  line `Tribunal or other authority shall be deemed to be income chargeable under the head “Capital gains”`
  line `of the previous year in which the final order of such court, Tribunal or other authority is made;]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 17, for “income under the head “Capital gains” of the previous year in which the transfer took`
  line `place” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
