obj_root_law_sections_264_content:
  string
  line 264
  line `46. Capital gains on distribution of assets by companies in liquidation. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in section, where the assets of a company are distributed to its shareholders on its`
  line `liquidation, such distribution shall not be regarded as a transfer by the company for the purposes`
  line `of section 45.`
  line `( 2 ) Where a shareholder on the liquidation of a company receives any money or other assets from the`
  line `company, he shall be chargeable to income- tax under the head “Capital gains”, in respect of the money so`
  line `received or the market value of the other assets on the date of distribution, as reduced by the amount`
  line `assessed as dividend within the meaning of sub-clause (c) of clause (22) of section 2 and the sum so`
  line `arrived at shall be deemed to be the full value of the consideration for the purposes of section 48.`
  line `1 [ 46A. Capital gains on purchase by company of its own shares or other specified securities. —`
  line `Where a shareholder or a holder of other specified securities receives any consideration from any`
  line `company for purchase of its own shares or other specified securities held by such shareholder or holder of`
  line `other specified securities, then, subject to the provisions of section 48, the difference between the cost of`
  line `acquisition and the value of consideration received by the shareholder or the holder of other specified`
  line `securities, as the case may be, shall be deemed to be the capital gains arising to such shareholder or the`
  line `holder of other specified securities, as the case may be, in the year in which such shares or other specified`
  line `securities were purchased by the company.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, “specified securities” shall have the me aning assigned`
  line `to it in Explanation to section 77A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).]`
  line `47. Transactions not regarded as transfer. — Nothing contained in section 45 shall apply to the`
  line `following transfers: —`
  line `( i ) any distribution of capital assets on the total or partial partition of a Hindu undivided family;`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `( iii ) any transfer of a capital asset under a gift or will or an irrevocable trust:`
  line `3 [Provided that this clause shall not apply to transfer under a gift or an irrevocable trust of a`
  line `capital asset being shares, debentures or warrants allotted by a company directly or indirectly to its`
  line `employees under 4 [any Employees’ Stock Option Plan or Scheme of the company offered to such`
  line `employees in accordance with the guidelines issued by the Central Government in this behalf];]`
  line `( iv ) any transfer of a capital asset by a company to its subsidiary company, if —`
  line `( a ) the parent company or its nominees hold the whole of the share capital of the subsidiary`
  line `company, and`
  line `( b ) the subsidiary company is an Indian company;`
  line `5 [( v ) any transfer of a capital asset by a subsidiary company to the holding company, if —`
  line `( a ) the whole of the share capital of the subsidiary company is held by the holding company,`
  line and
  line `( b ) the holding company is an Indian company:]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `2. Clause ( ii ) omitted by Act 11 of 1987, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 29, for “the Employees’ Stock option Plan or Scheme” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2001).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
