obj_root_law_sections_265_content:
  string
  line 265
  line `1 [Provided that nothing contained in clause ( iv ) or clause ( v ) shall apply to the transfer of a capital`
  line `asset made after the 29th day of February, 1988, as stock-in-trade;]`
  line `2 [( vi ) any transfer, in a scheme of amalgamation, of a capital asset by the amalgamating company`
  line `to the amalgamated company if the amalgamated company is an Indian company;`
  line `3 [( via ) any transfer, in a scheme of amalgamation, of a capital asset being a share or shares held in`
  line `an Indian company, by the amalgamating foreign company to the amalgamated foreign company, if —`
  line `( a ) at least twenty-five per cent of the shareholders of the amalgamating foreign company`
  line `continue to remain shareholders of the amalgamated foreign company, and`
  line `( b ) such transfer does not attract tax on capital gains in the country, in which the`
  line `amalgamating company is incorporated;]`
  line `4 [( viaa ) any transfer, in a scheme of amalgamation of a banking company with a banking`
  line `institution sanctioned and brought into force by the Central Government under sub-section ( 7 ) of`
  line `section 45 of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), of a capital asset by the banking`
  line `company to the banking institution.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( i ) “banking company” shall have the same meaning assigned to it in clause (c) of section 5`
  line `of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949);`
  line `( ii ) “banking institution” shall have the same meaning assigned to it in sub -section ( 15 ) of`
  line `section 45 of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949);]`
  line `5 [( viab ) any transfer, in a scheme of amalgamation, of a capital asset, being a share of a foreign`
  line `company, referred to in the Explanation 5 to clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 9, which derives,`
  line `directly or indirectly, its value substantially from the share or shares of an Indian company, held by`
  line `the amalgamating foreign company to the amalgamated foreign company, if —`
  line `( A ) at least twenty-five per cent. of the shareholders of the amalgamating foreign company`
  line `continue to remain shareholders of the amalgamated foreign company; and`
  line `( B ) such transfer does not attract tax on capital gains in the country in which the`
  line `amalgamating company is incorporated;]`
  line `6 [( vib ) any transfer, in a demerger, of a capital asset by the demerged company to the resulting`
  line `company, if the resulting company is an Indian company;`
  line `( vic ) any transfer in a demerger, of a capital asset, being a share or shares held in an Indian`
  line `company, by the demerged foreign company to the resulting foreign company, if —`
  line `( a ) the shareholders holding not less than three-fourths in value of the shares of the demerged`
  line `foreign company continue to remain shareholders of the resulting foreign company; and`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-1967).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
