obj_root_law_sections_266_content:
  string
  line 266
  line `( b ) such transfer does not attract tax on capital gains in the country, in which the demerged`
  line `foreign company is incorporated:`
  line `Provided that the provisions of sections 391 to 394 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)`
  line `shall not apply in case of demergers referred to in this clause;`
  line `1 [( vica ) any transfer in a business reorganisation, of a capital asset by the predecessor`
  line `co-operative bank to the successor co-operative bank;`
  line `( vicb ) any transfer by a shareholder, in a business reorganisation, of a capital asset being a share`
  line `or shares held by him in the predecessor co-operative bank if the transfer is made in consideration of`
  line `the allotment to him of any share or shares in the successor co-operative bank.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of clauses ( vica ) and ( vicb ), the expressions “business`
  line `reorganisation”, “predecessor co - operative bank” and “suc cessor co- operative bank” shall have the`
  line `meanings respectively assigned to them in section 44DB;]`
  line `2 [( vicc ) any transfer in a demerger, of a capital asset, being a share of a foreign company, referred`
  line `to in the Explanation 5 to clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 9, which derives, directly or`
  line `indirectly, its value substantially from the share or shares of an Indian company, held by the`
  line `demerged foreign company to the resulting foreign company, if —`
  line `( a ) the shareholders, holding not less than three-fourths in value of the shares of the`
  line `demerged foreign company, continue to remain shareholders of the resulting foreign company;`
  line and
  line `( b ) such transfer does not attract tax on capital gains in the country in which the demerged`
  line `foreign company is incorporated:`
  line `Provided that the provisions of sections 391 to 394 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)`
  line `shall not apply in case of demergers referred to in this clause;]`
  line `( vid ) any transfer or issue of shares by the resulting company, in a scheme of demerger to the`
  line `shareholders of the demerged company if the transfer or issue is made in consideration of demerger of`
  line `the undertaking;]`
  line `( vii ) any transfer by a shareholder, in a scheme of amalgamation, of a capital asset being a share`
  line `or shares held by him in the amalgamating company, if —`
  line `( a ) the transfer is made in consideration of the allotment to him of any share or shares in the`
  line `amalgamated company except where the shareholder itself is the amalgamated company, and`
  line `( b ) the amalgamated company is an Indian company;`
  line `3 [( viia ) any transfer of a capital asset, being bonds or 4 [Global Depository Receipts] referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115AC, made outside India by a non-resident to another non-resident;`
  line `5 [( viiaa ) any transfer, made outside India, of a capital asset being rupee denominated bond of an`
  line `Indian company outside India, by a non-resident to another non-resident;]`
  line `6 [( viiab ) any transfer of a capital asset, being —`
  line `( a ) bond or Global Depository Receipt referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115AC; or`
  line `( b ) rupee denominated bond of an Indian company; or`
  line `( c ) derivative,`
  line `made by a non-resident on a recognised stock exchange located in any International Financial Services`
  line `Centre and where the consideration for such transaction is paid or payable in foreign currency.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-6-1992).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 29, for “shares” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2002).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
