obj_root_law_sections_268_content:
  string
  line 268
  line `Provided that such transfer is made during the period commencing from the previous year in`
  line `which the said company has become a sick industrial company under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 17 of`
  line `that Act and ending with the previous year during which the entire net worth of such company`
  line `becomes equal to or exceeds the accumulated losses.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, “net worth” shall have the meaning assigned to it`
  line `in clause ( ga ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 3 of the Sick Industrial Companies (Special Provisions)`
  line `Act, 1985 (1 of 1986);]`
  line `1 [( xiii ) 2 [any transfer of a capital asset or intangible asset by a firm to a company as a result of`
  line `succession of the firm by a company in the business carried on by the firm, or any transfer of a capital`
  line `asset to a company in the course of 3 [demutualisation or corporatisation] of a recognised stock`
  line `exchange in India as a result of which an association of persons or body of individuals is succeeded`
  line `by such company:]`
  line `Provided that —`
  line `( a ) all the assets and liabilities of the firm or of the association of persons or body of`
  line `individuals relating to the business immediately before the succession become the assets and`
  line `liabilities of the company;`
  line `( b ) all the partners of the firm immediately before the succession become the shareholders of`
  line `the company in the same proportion in which their capital accounts stood in the books of the firm`
  line `on the date of the succession;`
  line `( c ) the partners of the firm do not receive any consideration or benefit, directly or indirectly,`
  line `in any form or manner, other than by way of allotment of shares in the company; and`
  line `( d ) the aggregate of the shareholding in the company of the partners of the firm is not less`
  line `than fifty per cent of the total voting power in the company and their shareholding continues to be`
  line `as such for a period of five years from the date of the succession;`
  line `4 [( e ) the 3 [demutualisation or corporatisation] of a recognised stock exchange in India is`
  line `carried out in accordance with a scheme for 3 [demutualisation or corporatisation] which is`
  line `approved by the Securities and Exchange Board of India established under section 3 of the`
  line `Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992);]`
  line `5 [( xiiia ) any transfer of a capital asset being a membership right held by a member of a`
  line `recognised stock exchange in India for acquisition of shares and trading or clearing rights acquired by`
  line `such member in that recognised stock exchange in accordance with a scheme for demutualisation or`
  line `corporatisation which is approved by the Securities and Exchange Board of India established under`
  line `section 3 of the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992);]`
  line `6 [( xiiib ) any transfer of a capital asset or intangible asset by a private company or unlisted public`
  line `company (hereafter in this clause referred to as the company) to a limited liability partnership or any`
  line `transfer of a share or shares held in the company by a shareholder as a result of conversion of the`
  line `company into a limited liability partnership in accordance with the provisions of section 56 or`
  line `section 57 of the Limited Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009):`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 21 (w.e.f.1-4-1999).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 29, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 30, for “corporatisation” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2004).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-2011).`
