  content obj_root_law_sections_269_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_269_footnotes
  sourcePage 269
obj_root_law_sections_269_content:
  string
  line 269
  line `Provided that —`
  line `( a ) all the assets and liabilities of the company immediately before the conversion become the`
  line `assets and liabilities of the limited liability partnership;`
  line `( b ) all the shareholders of the company immediately before the conversion become the`
  line `partners of the limited liability partnership and their capital contribution and profit sharing ratio`
  line `in the limited liability partnership are in the same proportion as their shareholding in the company`
  line `on the date of conversion;`
  line `( c ) the shareholders of the company do not receive any consideration or benefit, directly or`
  line `indirectly, in any form or manner, other than by way of share in profit and capital contribution in`
  line `the limited liability partnership;`
  line `( d ) the aggregate of the profit sharing ratio of the shareholders of the company in the limited`
  line `liability partnership shall not be less than fifty per cent at any time during the period of five years`
  line `from the date of conversion;`
  line `( e ) the total sales, turnover or gross receipts in the business of the company in any of the`
  line `three previous years preceding the previous year in which the conversion takes place does not`
  line `exceed sixty lakh rupees; 1 ***`
  line `2 [( ea ) the total value of the assets as appearing in the books of account of the company in any`
  line `of the three previous years preceding the previous year in which the conversion takes place does`
  line `not exceed five crore rupees; and]`
  line `( f ) no amount is paid, either directly or indirectly, to any partner out of balance of`
  line `accumulated profit standing in the accounts of the company on the date of conversion for a period`
  line `of three years from the date of conversion.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, the expressions “private company” and “unlisted`
  line `public company” shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in the Limited Liability`
  line `Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009);]`
  line `( xiv ) where a sole proprietary concern is succeeded by a company in the business carried on by it`
  line `as a result of which the sole proprietary concern sells or otherwise transfers any capital asset or`
  line `intangible asset to the company:`
  line `Provided that —`
  line `( a ) all the assets and liabilities of the sole proprietary concern relating to the business`
  line `immediately before the succession become the assets and liabilities of the company;`
  line `( b ) the shareholding of the sole proprietor in the company is not less than fifty per cent of the`
  line `total voting power in the company and his shareholding continues to remain as such for a period`
  line `of five years from the date of the succession; and`
  line `( c ) the sole proprietor does not receive any consideration or benefit, directly or indirectly, in`
  line `any form or manner, other than by way of allotment of shares in the company;`
  line `1. The word “and” omitted by Act 28 of 2016, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 28, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
