obj_root_law_sections_270_content:
  string
  line 270
  line `( xv ) any transfer in a scheme for lending of any securities under an agreement or arrangement,`
  line `which the assessee has entered into with the borrower of such securities and which is subject to the`
  line `guidelines issued by the Securities and Exchange Board of India, established under section 3 of the`
  line `Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992) 1 [or the Reserve Bank of India`
  line `constituted under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 3 of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934)], in`
  line `this regard;`
  line `2 [( xvi ) any transfer of a capital asset in a transaction of reverse mortgage under a scheme made`
  line `and notified by the Central Government;]`
  line `3 [( xvii ) any transfer of a capital asset, being share of a special purpose vehicle to a business trust`
  line `in exchange of units allotted by that trust to the transferor.`
  line `Explanation. — Fo r the purposes of this clause, the expression “special purpose vehicle” shall`
  line `have the meaning assigned to it in the Explanation to clause ( 23FC ) of section 10;]`
  line `4 [( xviii ) any transfer by a unit holder of a capital asset, being a unit or units, held by him in the`
  line `consolidating scheme of a mutual fund, made in consideration of the allotment to him of a capital`
  line `asset, being a unit or units, in the consolidated scheme of the mutual fund:`
  line `Provided that the consolidation is of two or more schemes of equity oriented fund or of two or`
  line `more schemes of a fund other than equity oriented fund.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( a ) “consolidated scheme” means the scheme with which the consolidating scheme merges or`
  line `which is formed as a result of such merger;`
  line `( b ) “consolidating scheme” means the scheme of a mutual fund which merges under the process`
  line `of consolidation of the schemes of mutual fund in accordance with the Securities and Exchange`
  line `Board of India (Mutual Funds) Regulations, 1996 made under the Securities and Exchange Board`
  line `of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992);`
  line `( c ) “equity oriented fund” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( 38 ) of section 10;`
  line `( d ) “mutual fund” means a mutual fund specified under clause ( 23D) of section 10.]`
  line `5 [( xix ) any transfer by a unit holder of a capital asset, being a unit or units, held by him in the`
  line `consolidating plan of a mutual fund scheme, made in consideration of the allotment to him of a`
  line `capital asset, being a unit or units, in the consolidated plan of that scheme of the mutual fund.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( a ) “consolidating plan” means the plan within a scheme of a mutual fund which merges`
  line `under the process of consolidation of the plans within a scheme of mutual fund in accordance`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
