obj_root_law_sections_272:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-272
  sectionNo (272)
  orderNo 272
  title `Page 272`
  content obj_root_law_sections_272_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_272_footnotes
  sourcePage 272
obj_root_law_sections_272_content:
  string
  line 272
  line `1 [48. Mode of computation. —The income chargeable under the head “Capital gains” shall be`
  line `computed, by deducting from the full value of the consideration received or accruing as a result of the`
  line `transfer of the capital asset the following amounts, namely: —`
  line `( i ) expenditure incurred wholly and exclusively in connection with such transfer;`
  line `( ii ) the cost of acquisition of the asset and the cost of any improvement thereto:`
  line `Provided that in the case of an assessee, who is a non-resident, capital gains arising from the transfer`
  line `of a capital asset being shares in, or debentures of, an Indian company shall be computed by converting`
  line `the cost of acquisition, expenditure incurred wholly and exclusively in connection with such transfer and`
  line `the full value of the consideration received or accruing as a result of the transfer of the capital asset into`
  line `the same foreign currency as was initially utilised in the purchase of the shares or debentures, and the`
  line `capital gains so computed in such foreign currency shall be reconverted into Indian currency, so,`
  line `however, that the aforesaid manner of computation of capital gains shall be applicable in respect of`
  line `capital gains accruing or arising from every reinvestment thereafter in, and sale of, shares in, or`
  line `debentures of, an Indian company:`
  line `Provided further that where long-term capital gain arises from the transfer of a long-term capital`
  line `asset, other than capital gain arising to a non-resident from the transfer of shares in, or debentures of, an`
  line `Indian company referred to in the first proviso, the provisions of clause ( ii ) shall have effect as if for the`
  line `words “cost of acquisition” and “cost of any improvement”, the words “indexed cost of acquisition” and`
  line `“indexed cost of any improvement” had respectively been substituted:`
  line `2 [Provided also that nothing contained in the first and second provisos shall apply to the capital gains`
  line `arising from the transfer of a long-term capital asset being an equity share in a company or a unit of an`
  line `equity oriented fund or a unit of a business trust referred to in section 112A:]`
  line `3 [Provided also that nothing contained in the second proviso shall apply to the long-term capital gain`
  line `arising from the transfer of a long-term capital asset, being a bond or debenture other than —`
  line `( a ) capital indexed bonds issued by the Government; or`
  line `( b ) Sovereign Gold Bond issued by the Reserve Bank of India under the Sovereign Gold Bond`
  line `Scheme, 2015:`
  line `Provided also that in case of an assessee being a non-resident, any gains arising on account of`
  line `appreciation of rupee against a foreign currency at the time of redemption of rupee denominated bond of`
  line `an Indian company 4 [held] by him, shall be ignored for the purposes of computation of full value of`
  line `consideration under this section:]`
  line `5 [Provided also that where shares, debentures or warrants referred to in the proviso to clause ( iii ) of`
  line `section 47 are transferred under a gift or an irrevocable trust, the market value on the date of such transfer`
  line `shall be deemed to be the full value of consideration received or accruing as a result of transfer for the`
  line `purposes of this section:]`
  line `6 [Provided also that no deduction shall be allowed in computing the income chargeable under the`
  line `head “Capital gains” in respect of any sum paid on account of securities transaction tax under Chapter VII`
  line `of the Finance (No. 2) Act, 2004 (23 of 2004).]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 24, for section 48 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 29, for the third proviso (w.e.f. 1-4-2017) which was earlier inserted by Act 26 of 1997,`
  line `s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 24 to read as “ subscribed ” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2018).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
