  content obj_root_law_sections_273_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_273_footnotes
  sourcePage 273
obj_root_law_sections_273_content:
  string
  line 273
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “foreign currency” and “Indian currency” shall have the meanings respectively assigned to`
  line `them in section 2 of 1 [the Foreign Exchange Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999);]`
  line `( ii ) the conversion of Indian currency into foreign currency and the reconversion of foreign`
  line `currency into Indian currency shall be at the rate of exchange prescribed in this behalf;`
  line `( iii ) “indexed cost of acquisition” means an amount which bears to the cost of acquisition the`
  line `same proportion as Cost Inflation Index for the year in which the asset is transferred bears to the Cost`
  line `Inflation Index for the first year in which the asset was held by the assessee or for the year beginning`
  line `on the 2 [1st day of April, 2001,] whichever is later;`
  line `( iv ) “indexed cost of any improvement” means an amount which bears to the cost of improvement`
  line `the same proportion as Cost Inflation Index for the year in which the asset is transferred bears to the`
  line `Cost Inflation Index for the year in which the improvement to the asset took place;`
  line `3 [( v ) “Cost Inflation Index”, in relation to a previous year, means such Index as the Central`
  line `Government may, having regard to seventy-five per cent of average rise in the 4 [Consumer Price`
  line `Index (urban)] for the immediately preceding previous year to such previous year, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, specify, in this behalf.]]`
  line `49. Cost with reference to certain modes of acquisition. — 5 [( 1 )] Where the capital asset became the`
  line `property of the assessee —`
  line `( i ) on any distribution of assets on the total or partial partition of a Hindu undivided family;`
  line `( ii ) under a gift or will;`
  line `( iii ) ( a ) by succession, inheritance or devolution, or`
  line `6 [( b ) on any distribution of assets on the dissolution of a firm, body of individuals, or other`
  line `association of persons, where such dissolution had taken place at any time before the 1st day of`
  line `April, 1987, or]`
  line `( c ) on any distribution of assets on the liquidation of a company, or`
  line `( d ) under a transfer to a revocable or an irrevocable trust, or`
  line `( e ) under any such transfer as is referred to in clause ( iv ) 7 [or clause ( v )] 8 [or clause ( vi )] 9 [or`
  line `clause ( via )] 10 [or clause ( viaa ) or clause ( viab ) or clause ( vib ) 11 [or clause ( vic )] or clause ( vica ) or`
  line `clause ( vicb ) or clause ( vicc )] 12 [or clause ( xiii ) or clause ( xiiib ) or clause ( xiv ) of section 47];`
  line `13 [( iv ) such assessee being a Hindu undivided family, by the mode referred to in sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 64 at any time after the 31st day of December, 1969,]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 4, for “the Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 24 for “1st day of April, 1981” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2018).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 22, for clause ( v ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 19, for “Consumer Price Index for U rban non- manual employees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2016).`
  line `5. Section 49 re-numbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 20 of 1967, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-1967).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 16, for sub-clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-1967).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 15, for “or clause ( viaa ) or clause ( vica ) or clause ( vicb )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2016).`
  line `11. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `12. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 16, for “clause ( xiiib ) of section 47” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1999).`
  line `13. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
