obj_root_law_sections_274_content:
  string
  line 274
  line `the cost of acquisition of the asset shall be deemed to be the cost for which the previous owner of the`
  line `property acquired it, as increased by the cost of any improvement of the assets incurred or borne by the`
  line `previous owner or the assessee, as the case may be.`
  line `1 [ Explanation. — In this 2 [sub- section] the expression “previous owner of the property” in relation to`
  line `any capital asset owned by an assessee means the last previous owner of the capital asset who acquired it`
  line `by a mode of acquisition other than that referred to in clause ( i ) or 3 [clause ( ii ) or clause ( iii ) or`
  line `clause ( iv )] of this 2 [sub-section].]`
  line `4 [( 2 ) Where the capital asset being a share or shares in an amalgamated company which is an Indian`
  line `company became the property of the assessee in consideration of a transfer referred to in clause ( vii ) of`
  line `section 47, the cost of acquisition of the asset shall be deemed to be the cost of acquisition to him of the`
  line `share or shares in the amalgamating company.]`
  line `5 [( 2A ) Where the capital asset, being a share or debenture of a company, became the property of the`
  line `assessee in consideration of a transfer referred to in clause ( x ) or clause ( xa ) of section 47, the cost of`
  line `acquisition of the asset to the assessee shall be deemed to be that part of the cost of debenture, debenture-`
  line `stock, bond or deposit certificate in relation to which such asset is acquired by the assessee.]`
  line `6 [( 2AA ) Where the capital gain arises from the transfer of specified security or sweat equity shares`
  line `referred to in sub-clause ( vi ) of clause ( 2 ) of section 17, the cost of acquisition of such security or shares`
  line `shall be the fair market value which has been taken into account for the purposes of the said sub-clause.]`
  line `7 [( 2AAA ) Where the capital asset, being rights of a partner referred to in section 42 of the Limited`
  line `Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009), became the property of the assessee on conversion as referred`
  line `to in clause ( xiiib ) of section 47, the cost of acquisition of the asset shall be deemed to be the cost of`
  line `acquisition to him of the share or shares in the company immediately before its conversion.]`
  line `8 [( 2AB ) Where the capital gain arises from the transfer of specified security or sweat equity shares,`
  line `the cost of acquisition of such security or shares shall be the fair market value which has been taken into`
  line `account while computing the value of fringe benefits under clause ( ba ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 115WC.]`
  line `9 [( 2ABB ) Where the capital asset, being share or shares of a company, is acquired by a non-resident`
  line `assessee on redemption of Global Depository Receipts referred to in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 115AC held by such assessee, the cost of acquisition of the share or shares shall be the price of`
  line `such share or shares prevailing on any recognised stock exchange on the date on which a request for such`
  line `redemption was made.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- section, “recognised stock exchange” shall have the`
  line `meaning assigned to it in clause ( ii ) of the Explanation 1 to sub-section ( 5 ) of section 43.]`
  line `10 [( 2AC ) Where the capital asset, being a unit of a business trust, became the property of the assessee`
  line `in consideration of a transfer as referred to in clause ( xvii ) of section 47, the cost of acquisition of the`
  line `asset shall be deemed to be the cost of acquisition to him of the share referred to in the said clause.]`
  line `9 [( 2AD ) Where the capital asset, being a unit or units in a consolidated scheme of a mutual fund,`
  line `became the property of the assessee in consideration of a transfer referred to in clause ( xviii ) of`
  line `section 47, the cost of acquisition of the asset shall be deemed to be the cost of acquisition to him of the`
  line `unit or units in the consolidating scheme of the mutual fund.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 20, for “section” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1967).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 12, for “clause ( ii ) or clause ( iii )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1976).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-1967).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 15, for sub-section ( 2A ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 23, for sub-section ( 2AA ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-2011).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 17 (w.e.f 1-4-2008).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
