  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_276_footnotes
  sourcePage 276
obj_root_law_sections_276_content:
  string
  line 276
  line `1 [( 6 ) Where the capital gain arises from the transfer of a specified capital asset referred to in clause ( c ) of`
  line `the Explanation to clause ( 37A ) of section 10, which has been transferred after the expiry of two years from`
  line `the end of the financial year in which the possession of such asset was handed over to the assessee, the cost of`
  line `acquisition of such specified capital asset shall be deemed to be its stamp duty value as on the last day of the`
  line `second financial year after the end of the financial year in which the possession of the said specified capital`
  line `asset was handed over to the assessee.`
  line `Explanation. –– For the purposes of this sub- section, “stamp duty value” means the value adopted or`
  line `assessed or assessable by any authority of the State Government for the purpose of payment of stamp duty`
  line `in respect of an immovable property.`
  line `( 7 ) Where the capital gain arises from the transfer of a capital asset, being share in the project, in the`
  line `form of land or building or both, referred to in sub-section ( 5A ) of section 45, not being the capital asset`
  line `referred to in the proviso to the said sub-section, the cost of acquisition of such asset, shall be the amount`
  line `which is deemed as full value of consideration in that sub-section;]`
  line `2 [( 8 ) Where the capital gain arises from the transfer of an asset, being the asset held by a trust or an`
  line `institution in respect of which accreted income has been computed and the tax has been paid thereon in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of Chapter XII-EB, the cost of acquisition of such asset shall be deemed to`
  line `be the fair market value of the asset which has been taken into account for computation of accreted`
  line `income as on the specified date referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) of section 115TD.”.]`
  line `3 [( 9 ) Where the capital gain arises from the transfer of a capital asset referred to in clause ( via ) of`
  line `section 28, the cost of acquisition of such asset shall be deemed to be the fair market value which has`
  line `been taken into account for the purposes of the said clause.]`
  line `4 [50. Special provision for computation of capital gains in case of depreciable assets. —`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in clause ( 42A ) of section 2, where the capital asset is an asset`
  line `forming part of a block of assets in respect of which depreciation has been allowed under this Act or`
  line `under the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922), the provisions of sections 48 and 49 shall be subject`
  line `to the following modifications: —`
  line `( 1 ) where the full value of the consideration received or accruing as a result of the transfer of the`
  line `asset together with the full value of such consideration received or accruing as a result of the transfer`
  line `of any other capital asset falling within the block of the assets during the previous year, exceeds the`
  line `aggregate of the following amounts, namely: —`
  line `( i ) expenditure incurred wholly and exclusively in connection with such transfer or transfers;`
  line `( ii ) the written down value of the block of assets at the beginning of the previous year; and`
  line `( iii ) the actual cost of any asset falling within the block of assets acquired during the`
  line `previous year,`
  line `such excess shall be deemed to be the capital gains arising from the transfer of short-term capital assets;`
  line `( 2 ) where any block of assets ceases to exist as such, for the reason that all the assets in that block are`
  line `transferred during the previous year, the cost of acquisition of the block of assets shall be the written`
  line `down value of the block of assets at the beginning of the previous year, as increased by the actual cost of`
  line `any asset falling within that block of assets, acquired by the assessee during the previous year and the`
  line `income received or accruing as a result of such transfer or transfers shall be deemed to be the capital gains`
  line `arising from the transfer of short-term capital assets.]`
  line `5 [50A. Special provision for cost of acquisition in case of depreciable asset. — Where the capital`
  line `asset is an asset in respect of which a deduction on account of depreciation under clause ( i ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 32 has been obtained by the assessee in any previous year, the provisions of`
  line `section 48 and 49 shall apply subject to the modification that the written down value, as defined in`
  line `clause ( 6 ) of section 43, of the asset, as adjusted, shall be taken as the cost of acquisition of the asset.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 25, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 9, for section 50 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
