  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_277_footnotes
  sourcePage 277
obj_root_law_sections_277_content:
  string
  line 277
  line `1 [50B. Special provision for computation of capital gains in case of slump sale. — ( 1 ) Any profits`
  line `or gains arising from the slump sale effected in the previous year shall be chargeable to income-tax as`
  line `capital gains arising from the transfer of long-term capital assets and shall be deemed to be the income of`
  line `the previous year in which the transfer took place:`
  line `Provided that any profits or gains arising from the transfer under the slump sale of any capital asset`
  line `being one or more undertakings owned and held by an assessee for not more than thirty-six months`
  line `immediately preceding the date of its transfer shall be deemed to be the capital gains arising from the`
  line `transfer of short-term capital assets.`
  line `( 2 ) In relation to capital assets being an undertaking or division transferred by way of such sale, the`
  line `“net worth” of the undertaking or the division, as the case may be, shall be deemed to be the cost of`
  line `acquisition and the cost of improvement for the purposes of section 48 and 49 and no regard shall be`
  line `given to the provisions contained in the second proviso to section 48.`
  line `(3) Every assessee, in the case of slump sale, shall furnish in the prescribed form along with the return`
  line `of income, a report of an accountant as defined in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288,`
  line `indicating the computation of the net worth of the undertaking or division, as the case may be, and`
  line `certifying that the net worth of the undertaking or division, as the case may be, has been correctly arrived`
  line `at in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line `2 [ Explanation 1. —For the purposes of this section, “net worth” shall be the aggregate value of total`
  line `assets of the undertaking or division as reduced by the value of liabilities of such undertaking or division`
  line `as appearing in its books of account:`
  line `Provided that any change in the value of assets on account of revaluation of assets shall be ignored for`
  line `the purposes of computing the net worth.`
  line `Explanation 2. — For computing the net worth, the aggregate value of total assets shall be, —`
  line `( a ) in the case of depreciable assets, the written down value of the block of assets determined in`
  line `accordance with the provisions contained in sub-item ( C ) of item ( i ) of sub-clause ( c ) of`
  line `clause ( 6 ) of section 43; 3 ***`
  line `4 [( b ) in the case of capital assets in respect of which the whole of the expenditure has been`
  line `allowed or is allowable as a deduction under section 35AD, nil; and`
  line `( c ) in the case of other assets, the book value of such assets.]]]`
  line `5 [50C. Special provision for full value of consideration in certain cases. — ( 1 ) Where the`
  line `consideration received or accruing as a result of the transfer by an assessee of a capital asset, being land`
  line `or building or both, is less than the value adopted 6 [or assessed or assessable] by any authority of a State`
  line `Government (hereafter in this section referred to as the “stamp valuation authority”) for the purpose of`
  line `payment of stamp duty in respect of such transfer, the value so adopted 6 [or assessed or assessable] shall,`
  line `for the purposes of section 48, be deemed to be the full value of the consideration received or accruing as`
  line `a result of such transfer.]`
  line `7 [Provided that where the date of the agreement fixing the amount of consideration and the date of`
  line `registration for the transfer of the capital asset are not the same, the value adopted or assessed or`
  line `assessable by the stamp valuation authority on the date of agreement may be taken for the purposes of`
  line `computing full value of consideration for such transfer:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 24, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `3. The word “and” omitted by Act 33 of 2009, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1 -4-2010).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 24, ibid., for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 25, for “or assessed” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2009).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 31 ( w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_277_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_278:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-278
  sectionNo (278)
  orderNo 278
  title `Page 278`
  content obj_root_law_sections_278_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_278_footnotes
  sourcePage 278
obj_root_law_sections_278_content:
  string
  line 278
  line `Provided further that the first proviso shall apply only in a case where the amount of consideration, or`
  line `a part thereof, has been received by way of an account payee cheque or account payee bank draft or by`
  line `use of electronic clearing system through a bank account, on or before the date of the agreement for`
  line transfer.]
  line `1 [Provided also that where the value adopted or assessed or assessable by the stamp valuation`
  line `authority does not exceed one hundred and five per cent. of the consideration received or accruing as a`
  line `result of the transfer, the consideration so received or accruing as a result of the transfer shall, for the`
  line `purposes of section 48, be deemed to be the full value of the consideration.]`
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ), where —`
  line `( a ) the assessee claims before any Assessing Officer that the value adopted 2 [or assessed or`
  line `assessable] by the stamp valuation authority under sub-section ( 1 ) exceeds the fair market value of`
  line `the property as on the date of transfer;`
  line `( b ) the value so adopted 2 [or assessed or assessable] by the stamp valuation authority under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) has not been disputed in any appeal or revision or no reference has been made before`
  line `any other authority, court or the High Court,`
  line `the Assessing Officer may refer the valuation of the capital asset to a Valuation Officer and where any`
  line `such reference is made, the provisions of sub-sections ( 2 ), ( 3 ), ( 4 ), ( 5 ) and ( 6 ) of section 16A, clause ( i ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) and sub-sections ( 6 ) and ( 7 ) of section 23A, sub-section ( 5 ) of section 24, section 34AA,`
  line `section 35 and section 37 of the Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957), shall, with necessary modifications,`
  line `apply in relation to such reference as they apply in relation to a reference made by the Assessing Officer`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 16A of that Act.`
  line `3 [ Explanation 1.] —For the purposes of this section, “Valuation Officer” shall have the same meaning`
  line `as in clause ( r ) of section 2 of the Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957).`
  line `4 [ Explanation 2. —For the purposes of this section, the expression “assessable” means the price which`
  line `the stamp valuation authority would have, notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any other`
  line `law for the time being in force, adopted or assessed, if it were referred to such authority for the purposes`
  line `of the payment of stamp duty.]`
  line `( 3 ) Subject to the provisions contained in sub-section ( 2 ), where the value ascertained under`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) exceeds the value adopted 2 [or assessed or assessable] by the stamp valuation authority`
  line `referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), the value so adopted 2 [or assessed or assessable] by such authority shall be`
  line `taken as the full value of the consideration received or accruing as a result of the transfer.]`
  line `5 [ 50CA. Special provision for full value of consideration for transfer of share other than quoted`
  line `share. — ( 1 ) Where the consideration received or accruing as a result of the transfer by an assessee of a`
  line `capital asset, being share of a company other than a quoted share, is less than the fair market value of such`
  line `share determined in such manner as may be prescribed, the value so determined shall, for the purposes of`
  line `section 48, be deemed to be the full value of consideration received or accruing as a result of such transfer.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, “quoted share” means the share quoted on any`
  line `recognised stock exchange with regularity from time to time, where the quotation of such share is based`
  line `on current transaction made in the ordinary course of business.]`
  line `6 [50D. Fair market value deemed to be full value of consideration in certain cases. — Where the`
  line `consideration received or accruing as a result of the transfer of a capital asset by an assessee is not`
  line `ascertainable or cannot be determined, then, for the purpose of computing income chargeable to tax as`
  line `capital gains, the fair market value of the said asset on the date of transfer shall be deemed to be the full`
  line `value of the consideration received or accruing as a result of such transfer.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 25, for “or assessed” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2009).`
  line `3. The Explanation renumbered as Explanation 1 thereof by s. 25, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-2009).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 25, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-2009).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
