  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_279_footnotes
  sourcePage 279
obj_root_law_sections_279_content:
  string
  line 279
  line `51. Advance money received. — Where any capital asset was on any previous occasion the subject of`
  line `negotiations for its transfer, any advance or other money received and retained by the assessee in respect`
  line `of such negotiations shall be deducted from the cost for which the asset was acquired or the written down`
  line `value or the fair market value, as the case may be, in computing the cost of acquisition:`
  line `1 [Provided that where any sum of money, received as an advance or otherwise in the course of`
  line `negotiations for transfer of a capital asset, has been included in the total income of the assessee for any`
  line `previous year in accordance with the provisions of clause ( ix ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 56, then, such`
  line `sum shall not be deducted from the cost for which the asset was acquired or the written down value or the`
  line `fair market value, as the case may be, in computing the cost of acquisition.]`
  line `52. [ Consideration for transfer in cases of understatement.] — Omitted by the Finance Act, 1987 (11`
  line `of 1987), s. 17 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988). Earlier amended by Act 5 of 1964, s. 13 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1964), Act 25 of`
  line `1975, s. 9 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1974) and Act 19 of 1978, s. 9 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line `53. [ Exemption of capital gains from a residential house.] — Omitted by the Finance Act, 1992 (18 of`
  line `1992), s. 26 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1993). Earlier substituted by Act 67 of 1984, s. 15 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1985) and amended`
  line `by Act 11 of 1987, s. 18 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `54. Profit on sale of property used for residence. — 2 [( 1 )] 3 [ 4 [Subject to the provisions of`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ), where, in the case of an assessee being an individual or a Hindu undivided family], the`
  line `capital gain arises from the transfer of a long-term capital asset 5 ***, being buildings or lands appurtenant`
  line `thereto, and being a residential house, the income of which is chargeable under the h ead “Income from`
  line `house property” (hereafter in this section referred to as the original asset), and the assessee has within a`
  line `period of 6 [one year before or two years after the date on which the transfer took place purchased], or has`
  line `within a period of three years after that date 7 [constructed, one residential house in India], then], instead`
  line `of the capital gain being charged to income-tax as income of the previous year in which the transfer took`
  line `place, it shall be dealt with in accordance with the following provisions of this section, that is to say, —`
  line `( i ) if the amount of the capital gain 8 [is greater than the cost of 9 [the residential house] so`
  line `purchased or constructed (hereafter in this section referred to as the new asset)], the difference`
  line `between the amount of the capital gain and the cost of the new asset shall be charged under section 45`
  line `as the income of the previous year; and for the purpose of computing in respect of the new asset any`
  line `capital gain arising from its transfer within a period of three years of its purchase or construction, as`
  line `the case may be, the cost shall be nil; or`
  line `( ii ) if the amount of the capital gain is equal to or less than the cost of the new asset, the capital`
  line `gain shall not be charged under section 45; and for the purpose of computing in respect of the new`
  line `asset any capital gain arising from its transfer within a period of three years of its purchase or`
  line `construction, as the case may be, the cost shall be reduced by the amount of the capital gain.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `2. Section 54 renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 19 of 1978, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 14 of 1982, s. 11, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-1983).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 19, for “Where, in the case of an assessee being an individual” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. The words and figures “to which the provisions of section 53 are not applicable” omitted by Act 32 of 1985, s. 14`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 23 of 1986, s. 11, for “one year before or after the date on which the transfer took place purchased”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 22, for “constructed, a residential house” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2015).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 19 of 1978, s. 10, for “is greater than the cost of the new asset” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1974).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 14 of 1982, s. 11, for “the house property” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1983).`
