obj_root_law_sections_280_content:
  string
  line 280
  line `1 [Provided that where the amount of the capital gain does not exceed two crore rupees, the`
  line `assessee, may at his option, purchase or construct two residential houses in India, and where such an`
  line `option has been exercised, ––`
  line `( a ) the provisions of this sub-section shall have effect as if f or the words “one residential`
  line `house in India”, the words “two residential houses in India” had been substituted;`
  line `( b ) any reference in this sub-section and sub-section ( 2 ) to “new asset” shall be construed as a`
  line `reference to the two residential houses in India: Provided further that where during any`
  line `assessment year, the assessee has exercised the option referred to in the first proviso, he shall not`
  line `be subsequently entitled to exercise the option for the same or any other assessment year.]`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `3 [( 2 ) The amount of the capital gain which is not appropriated by the assessee towards the purchase of`
  line `the new asset made within one year before the date on which the transfer of the original asset took place,`
  line `or which is not utilised by him for the purchase or construction of the new asset before the date of`
  line `furnishing the return of income under section 139, shall be deposited by him before furnishing such`
  line `return [such deposit being made in any case not later than the due date applicable in the case of the`
  line `assessee for furnishing the return of income under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139] in an account in any`
  line `such bank or institution as may be specified in, and utilised in accordance with, any scheme which the`
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, frame in this behalf and such return`
  line `shall be accompanied by proof of such deposit; and, for the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), the amount, if`
  line `any, already utilised by the assessee for the purchase or construction of the new asset together with the`
  line `amount so deposited shall be deemed to be the cost of the new asset:`
  line `Provided that if the amount deposited under this sub-section is not utilised wholly or partly for the`
  line `purchase or construction of the new asset within the period specified in sub-section ( 1 ), then, —`
  line `( i ) the amount not so utilised shall be charged under section 45 as the income of the previous`
  line `year in which the period of three years from the date of the transfer of the original asset expires; and`
  line `( ii ) the assessee shall be entitled to withdraw such amount in accordance with the scheme`
  line aforesaid.
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `54A. [ Relief of tax on capital gains in certain cases. ] — Omitted by the Finance ( No. 2) Act, 1971 (32`
  line `of 1971), s. 11 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1972). Earlier inserted by Act 10 of 1965, s. 17 (1-4-1965). Again inserted by`
  line `Act 4 of 1988, s. 16 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988) and omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5 [54B. Capital gain on transfer of land used for agricultural purposes not to be charged in`
  line `certain cases. — 6 [( 1 )] 7 [Subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ), where the capital gain arises] from`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2020).`
  line `2. The Explanation omitted by Act 11 of 1987, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for sub-section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `4. The Explanation omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 19 of 1970, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1970).`
  line `6. Section 54B renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 19 of 1978, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 20, for “Where the capital gain arises” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
