obj_root_law_sections_281_content:
  string
  line 281
  line `the transfer of a capital asset being land which, in the two years immediately preceding the date on which`
  line `the transfer took place, was being used by 1 [the assessee being an individual or his parent, or a Hindu`
  line `undivided family] for agricultural purposes 2 [(hereinafter referred to as the original asset)], and the`
  line `assessee has, within a period of two years after that date, purchased any other land for being used for`
  line `agricultural purposes, then, instead of the capital gain being charged to income-tax as income of the`
  line `previous year in which the transfer took place, it shall be dealt with in accordance with the following`
  line `provisions of this section, that is to say, —`
  line `( i ) if the amount of the capital gain is greater than the cost of the land so purchased (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as the new asset), the difference between the amount of the capital gain and the cost of the`
  line `new asset shall be charged under section 45 as the income of the previous year; and for the purpose of`
  line `computing in respect of the new asset any capital gain arising from its transfer within a period of`
  line `three years of its purchase, the cost shall be nil; or`
  line `( ii ) if the amount of the capital gain is equal to or less than the cost of the new asset, the capital`
  line `gain shall not be charged under section 45; and for the purpose of computing in respect of the new`
  line `asset any capital gain arising from its transfer within a period of three years of its purchase, the cost`
  line `shall be reduced, by the amount of the capital gain.]`
  line `3 [( 2 ) The amount of the capital gain which is not utilised by the assessee for the purchase of the new`
  line `asset before the date of furnishing the return of income under section 139, shall be deposited by him`
  line `before furnishing such return [such deposit being made in any case not later than the due date applicable`
  line `in the case of the assessee for furnishing the return of income under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139] in an`
  line `account in any such bank or institution as may be specified in, and utilised in accordance with, any`
  line `scheme which the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, frame in this behalf`
  line `and such return shall be accompanied by proof of such deposit; and, for the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ),`
  line `the amount, if any, already utilised by the assessee for the purchase of the new asset together with the`
  line `amount so deposited shall be deemed to be the cost of the new asset:`
  line `Provided that if the amount deposited under this sub-section is not utilised wholly or partly for the`
  line `purchase of the new asset within the period specified in sub-section ( 1 ), then, —`
  line `( i ) the amount not so utilised shall be charged under section 45as the income of the previous year`
  line `in which the period of two years from the date of the transfer of the original asset expires; and`
  line `( ii ) the assessee shall be entitled to withdraw such amount in accordance with the scheme`
  line aforesaid.
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `54C. [Capital gain on transfer of jewellery held for personal use not to be charged in certain cases. ] —`
  line `Omitted by the Finance Act, 1976 (66 of 1976) ( w.e.f. 1-4-1976). Earlier inserted by Act 16 of 1972, s. 9`
  line `( w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 18, for “the assessee or a parent of his” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 19 of 1978, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 20, for sub-section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `4. The Explanation omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
