  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_282_footnotes
  sourcePage 282
obj_root_law_sections_282_content:
  string
  line 282
  line `1 [54D. Capital gain on compulsory acquisition of lands and buildings not to be charged in`
  line `certain cases. — 2 [( 1 )] 3 [Subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ), where the capital gain arises] from`
  line `the transfer by way of compulsory acquisition under any law of a capital asset, being land or building or`
  line `any right in land or building, forming part of an industrial undertaking belonging to the assessee which, in`
  line `the two years immediately preceding the date on which the transfer took place, was being used by the`
  line `assessee for the purposes of the business of the said undertaking 4 [(hereafter in this section referred to as`
  line `the original asset)], and the assessee has within a period of three years after that date purchased any other`
  line `land or building or any right in any other land or building or constructed any other building for the`
  line `purposes of shifting or re-establishing the said undertaking or setting up another industrial undertaking,`
  line `then, instead of the capital gain being charged to income-tax as the income of the previous year in which`
  line `the transfer took place, it shall be dealt with in accordance with the following provisions of this section,`
  line `that is to say, —`
  line `( i ) if the amount of the capital gain is greater than the cost of the land, building or right so`
  line `purchased or the building so constructed (such land, building or right being hereafter in this section`
  line `referred to as the new asset), the difference between the amount of the capital gain and the cost of the`
  line `new asset shall be charged under section 45 as the income of the previous year; and for the purpose of`
  line `computing in respect of the new asset any capital gain arising from its transfer within a period of`
  line `three years of its purchase or construction, as the case may be, the cost shall be nil; or`
  line `( ii ) if the amount of the capital gain is equal to or less than the cost of the new asset, the capital`
  line `gain shall not be charged under section 45; and for the purpose of computing in respect of the new`
  line `asset any capital gain arising from its transfer within a period of three years of its purchase or`
  line `construction, as the case may be, the cost shall be reduced by the amount of the capital gain.]`
  line `5 [( 2 ) The amount of the capital gain which is not utilised by the assessee for the purchase or`
  line `construction of the new asset before the date of furnishing the return of income under section 139,shall be`
  line `deposited by him before furnishing such return [such deposit being made in any case not later than the`
  line `due date applicable in the case of the assessee for furnishing the return of income under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 139] in an account in any such bank or institution as may be specified in, and utilised in`
  line `accordance with, any scheme which the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `frame in this behalf and such return shall be accompanied by proof of such deposit; and, for the purposes`
  line `of sub-section ( 1 ), the amount, if any, already utilised by the assessee for the purchase or construction of`
  line `the new asset together with the amount so deposited shall be deemed to be the cost of the new asset:`
  line `Provided that if the amount deposited under this sub-section is not utilised wholly or partly for the`
  line `purchase or construction of the new asset within the period specified in sub-section ( 1 ), then, —`
  line `( i ) the amount not so utilised shall be charged under section 45as the income of the previous year`
  line `in which the period of three years from the date of the transfer of the original asset expires; and`
  line `( ii ) the assessee shall be entitled to withdraw such amount in accordance with the scheme`
  line aforesaid.
  line `6 * * * * *`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1973, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line `2. Section 54D numbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 19 of 1978, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 21, for “Where the capital gain arises” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4 Ins. by Act 19 of 1978, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 21, for sub-section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `6. The Explanation omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
