obj_root_law_sections_283_content:
  string
  line 283
  line `1 [54E. Capital gain on transfer of capital not to be assets charged in certain cases. — ( 1 ) Where`
  line `the capital gain arises from the transfer of a 2 [long-term capital asset] 3 [before the 1st day of April, 1992],`
  line `(the capital asset so transferred being hereafter in this section referred to as the original asset) and the`
  line `assessee has, within a period of six months after the date of such transfer, invested or deposited the`
  line `4 [whole or any part of the net consideration] in any specified asset (such specified asset being hereafter in`
  line `this section referred to as the new asset), the capital gain shall be dealt with in accordance with the`
  line `following provisions of this section, that is to say, —`
  line `( a ) if the cost of the new asset is not less than the 5 [net consideration] in respect of the original`
  line `asset, the whole of such capital gain shall not be charged under section 45;`
  line `( b ) if the cost of the new asset is less than the 5 [net consideration] in respect of the original asset,`
  line `so much of the capital gain as bears to the whole of the capital gain the same proportion as the cost of`
  line `acquisition of the new asset bears to the 6 [net consideration] shall not be charged under section 45:`
  line `7 [Provided that in a case where the original asset is transferred after the 28th day of February, 1983,`
  line `the provisions of this sub-section shall not apply unless the assessee has invested or deposited the whole`
  line `or, as the case may be, any part of the net consideration in the new asset by initially subscribing to such`
  line `new asset:]`
  line `8 [Provided further that in a case where the transfer of the original asset is by way of compulsory`
  line `acquisition under any law and the full amount of compensation awarded for such acquisition is not`
  line `received by the assessee on the date of such transfer, the period of six months referred to in this`
  line `sub-section shall, in relation to so much of such compensation as is not received on the date of the`
  line `transfer, be reckoned from the date immediately following the date on which such compensation is`
  line `received by the assessee 9 [or the 31st day of March, 1992, whichever is earlier].]`
  line `Explanation 1. — 10 [For the purposes of this sub- section, “specified asset” means,—`
  line `( a ) in a case where the original asset is transferred before the 1st day of March, 1979, any of the`
  line `following assets, namely: — ]`
  line `( i ) securities of the Central Government or a State Government;`
  line `( ii ) savings certificates as defined in clause ( c ) of section 2 of the Government Savings`
  line `Certificates Act, 1959 (46 of 1959);`
  line `( iii ) units in the Unit Trust of India established under the Unit Trust of India`
  line `Act, 1963 (52 of 1963);`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-1978).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 22, for “ca pital asset, not being a short- term capital asset” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 21 of 1979, s. 8, for “full value of the consideration or any part thereof received or accruing as a result o f`
  line `such tr ansfer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1979).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for “full value of consideration received or accruing” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1979).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for “full value of such consideration” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1979).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 11 of 1983, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-1983).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-1984).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 21 of 1979, s. 8, for ‘For the purposes of this sub -section and sub-section ( 3 ), “specified asset” means any`
  line `of the following assets, namely: —’(w.e.f. 1 -4-1979).`
obj_root_law_sections_283_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_284:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-284
