obj_root_law_sections_287_content:
  string
  line 287
  line `1 [54EA. Capital gain on transfer of long-term capital assets not to be charged in the case of`
  line `investment in 2 [specified securities]. — ( 1 ) Where the capital gain arises from the transfer of a long-term`
  line `capital asset 3 [before the 1st day of April, 2000] (the capital asset so transferred being hereafter in this`
  line `section referred to as the original asset) and the assessee has, at any time within a period of six months`
  line `after the date of such transfer, invested the whole or any part of the net consideration in any of the`
  line `4 [bonds, debentures, shares of a public company or units of any mutual fund referred to in clause ( 23D )`
  line `of section 10,]specified by the Board in this behalf by notification in the Official Gazette (such assets`
  line `hereafter in this section referred to as the 2 [specified securities]), the capital gain shall be dealt with in`
  line `accordance with the following provisions of this section, that is to say, —`
  line `( a ) if the cost of the 2 [specified securities] is not less than the net consideration in respect of the`
  line `original asset, the whole of such capital gain shall not be charged under section 45;`
  line `( b ) if the cost of the 2 [specified securities] is less than the net consideration in respect of the`
  line `original asset, so much of the capital gain as bears to the whole of the capital gain the same`
  line `proportion as the cost of acquisition of the 2 [specified securities] bears to the net consideration shall`
  line `not be charged under section 45.`
  line `( 2 ) Where the 2 [specified securities] are transferred or converted (otherwise than by transfer) into`
  line `money at any time within a period of three years from the date of their acquisition, the amount of capital`
  line `gain arising from the transfer of the original asset not charged under section 45 on the basis of the cost of`
  line `such 2 [specified securities] as provided in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to be`
  line `the income chargeable under the head “Capital gains” relating to long -term capital assets of the previous`
  line `year in which the 2 [specified securities] are transferred or converted (otherwise than by transfer) into`
  line money.
  line `Explanation. — In a case where the original asset is transferred and the assessee invests the whole or`
  line `any part of the net consideration in respect of the original asset in any 2 [specified securities] and such`
  line `assessee takes any loan or advance on the security of such 2 [specified securities], he shall be deemed to`
  line `have converted (otherwise than by transfer) such 2 [specified securities] into money on the date on which`
  line `such loan or advance is taken.`
  line `( 3 ) Where the cost of the 2 [specified securities] has been taken into account for the purposes of`
  line `clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ), a rebate with reference to such cost shall not be allowed under`
  line `section 88.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “cost”, in relation to a ny 2 [specified securities], means the amount invested in such 2 [specified`
  line `securities] out of the net consideration received or accruing as a result of the transfer of the original`
  line asset;
  line `( b ) “net consideration”, in relation to the transfer of a capital ass et, means the full value of the`
  line `consideration received or accruing as a result of the transfer of the capital asset as reduced by the`
  line `expenditure incurred wholly and exclusively in connection with such transfer.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-10-1996).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 1997, s. 2, for “specified bonds or debentures” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1996).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 14 of 1997, s. 2, for “bonds, debentures or units of any mutual fund refe rred to in clause (23D) of`
  line `section 10” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1996).`
