obj_root_law_sections_288_content:
  string
  line 288
  line `54EB. Capital gain on transfer of long-term capital assets not to be charged in certain`
  line `cases. — ( 1 ) Where the capital gain arises from the transfer of a long-term capital asset 1 [before the 1st day`
  line `of April, 2000] (the capital asset so transferred being hereafter in this section referred to as the original`
  line `asset), and the assessee has, at any time within a period of six months after the date of such transfer`
  line `invested the whole or any part of capital gains, in any of the assets specified by the Board in this behalf`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette (such assets hereafter in this section referred to as the long-term`
  line `specified assets), the capital gain shall be dealt with in accordance with the following provisions of this`
  line `section, that is to say, —`
  line `( a ) if the cost of the long-term specified asset is not less than the capital gain arising from the`
  line `transfer of the original asset, the whole of such capital gain shall not be charged under section 45;`
  line `( b ) if the cost of the long-term specified asset is less than the capital gain arising from the transfer`
  line `of the original asset, so much of the capital gain as bears to the whole of the capital gain the same`
  line `proportion as the cost of acquisition of the long-term specified asset bears to the whole of the capital`
  line `gain, shall not be charged under section 45.`
  line `Explanation. —“Cost”, in relation to any long -term specified asset, means the amount invested in`
  line `such specified asset out of capital gains received or accruing as a result of the transfer of the original`
  line asset.
  line `( 2 ) Where the long-term specified asset is transferred or converted (otherwise than by transfer) into`
  line `money at any time within a period of seven years from the date of its acquisition, the amount of capital`
  line `gains arising from the transfer of the original asset not charged under section 45 on the basis of the cost of`
  line `such long-term specified asset as provided in clause ( a ), or as the case may be, clause ( b ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to be the income chargeable under the head “Capital gains” relating to`
  line `long-term capital assets of the previous year in which the long-term specified asset is transferred or`
  line `converted (otherwise than by transfer) into money.`
  line `Explanation. — In a case where the original asset is transferred and the assessee invests the whole or`
  line `any part of the capital gain received or accrued as a result of transfer of the original asset in any long-term`
  line `specified asset and such assessee takes any loan or advance on the security of such specified asset, he`
  line `shall be deemed to have converted (otherwise than by transfer) such specified asset into money on the`
  line `date on which such loan or advance is taken.`
  line `( 3 ) Where the cost of the long-term specified asset has been taken into account for the purposes of`
  line `clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ), a deduction from the amount of income-tax with reference to`
  line `such cost shall not be allowed under section 88.]`
  line `2 [54EC. Capital gain not to be charged on investment in certain bonds. — ( 1 ) Where the capital`
  line `gain arises from the transfer of a long-term capital asset 3 [, being land or building or both,] (the capital`
  line `asset so transferred being hereafter in this section referred to as the original asset) and the assessee has, at`
  line `any time within a period of six months after the date of such transfer, invested the whole or any part of`
  line `capital gains in the long-term specified asset, the capital gain shall be dealt with in accordance with the`
  line `following provisions of this section, that is to say, —`
  line `( a ) if the cost of the long-term specified asset is not less than the capital gain arising from the`
  line `transfer of the original asset, the whole of such capital gain shall not be charged under section 45;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 27, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
