obj_root_law_sections_289_content:
  string
  line 289
  line `( b ) if the cost of the long-term specified asset is less than the capital gain arising from the transfer`
  line `of the original asset, so much of the capital gain as bears to the whole of the capital gain the same`
  line `proportion as the cost of acquisition of the long-term specified asset bears to the whole of the capital`
  line `gain, shall not be charged under section 45:`
  line `1 [Provided that the investment made on or after the 1st day of April, 2007 in the long-term specified`
  line `asset by an assessee during any financial year does not exceed fifty lakh rupees:]`
  line `2 [Provided further that the investment made by an assessee in the long-term specified asset, from`
  line `capital gains arising from transfer of one or more original assets, during the financial year in which the`
  line `original asset or assets are transferred and in the subsequent financial year does not exceed fifty lakh`
  line rupees.]
  line `( 2 ) Where the long-term specified asset is transferred or converted (otherwise than by transfer) into`
  line `money at any time within a period of three years from the date of its acquisition, the amount of capital`
  line `gains arising from the transfer of the original asset not charged under section 45 on the basis of the cost of`
  line `such long-term specified asset as provided in clause ( a ) or, as the case may be, clause ( b ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to be the income chargeable under the head “Capital gains” relating to`
  line `long-term capital asset of the previous year in which the long-term specified asset is transferred or`
  line `converted (otherwise than by transfer) into money.`
  line `3 [Provided that in case of long-term specified asset referred to in subclause ( ii ) of clause ( ba ) of the`
  line `Explanation occurring after sub-section ( 3 ), this sub-section shall have effect as if for the words “ three`
  line `years ”, the words “ five years ” had been substituted.]`
  line `Explanation. — In a case where the original asset is transferred and the assessee invests the whole or`
  line `any part of the capital gain received or accrued as a result of transfer of the original asset in any long-term`
  line `specified asset and such assessee takes any loan or advance on the security of such specified asset, he`
  line `shall be deemed to have converted (otherwise than by transfer) such specified asset into money on the`
  line `date on which such loan or advance is taken.`
  line `4 [( 3 ) Where the cost of the long-term specified asset has been taken into account for the purposes of`
  line `clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ), —`
  line `( a ) a deduction from the amount of income-tax with reference to such cost shall not be allowed`
  line `under section 88 for any assessment year ending before the 1st day of April, 2006;`
  line `( b ) a deduction from the income with reference to such cost shall not be allowed under section`
  line `80C for any assessment year beginning on or after the 1st day of April, 2006.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “cost”, in relation to any long -term specified asset, means the amount invested in such`
  line `specified asset out of capital gains received or accruing as a result of the transfer of the original`
  line asset;
  line `5 [( b ) “long - term specified asset” for making any investment under this section during the`
  line `period commencing from the 1st day of April, 2006 and ending with the 31st day of March, 2007,`
  line `means any bond, redeemable after three years and issued on or after the 1st day of April, 2006,`
  line `but on or before the 31st day of March, 2007, —`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 18, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
