obj_root_law_sections_291_content:
  string
  line 291
  line `( ii ) “ listed securities ” shall have the same meaning as in clause ( a ) of the Explanation to`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 112;`
  line `( iii ) “unit” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( b ) of the Explanation to`
  line `section 115AB.`
  line `( 2 ) Where the specified equity shares are sold or otherwise transferred within a period of one year`
  line `from the date of their acquisition, the amount of capital gain arising from the transfer of the original asset`
  line `not charged under section 45 on the basis of the cost of such specified equity shares as provided in clause`
  line `( a ) or, as the case may be, clause ( b ), of sub-section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to be the income chargeable`
  line `under the head “Capital gains” relating to long -term capital assets of the previous year in which such`
  line `equity shares are sold or otherwise transferred.`
  line `1 [( 3 ) Where the cost of the specified equity shares has been taken into account for the purposes of`
  line `clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ), —`
  line `( a ) a deduction from the amount of income-tax with reference to such cost shall not be allowed`
  line `under section 88 for any assessment year ending before the 1st day of April, 2006;`
  line `( b ) a deduction from the income with reference to such cost shall not be allowed under section`
  line `80C for any assessment year beginning on or after the 1st day of April, 2006.]]`
  line `2 [54EE. Capital gain not to be charged on investment in units of a specified fund. — ( 1 ) Where`
  line `the capital gain arises from the transfer of a long-term capital asset (herein in this section referred to as`
  line `the original asset) and the assessee has, at any time within a period of six months after the date of such`
  line `transfer, invested the whole or any part of capital gains in the long-term specified asset, the capital gain`
  line `shall be dealt with in accordance with the following provisions of this section, namely: —`
  line `( a ) if the cost of the long-term specified asset is not less than the capital gain arising from the`
  line `transfer of the original asset, the whole of such capital gain shall not be charged under section 45;`
  line `( b ) if the cost of the long-term specified asset is less than the capital gain arising from the`
  line `transfer of the original asset, so much of the capital gain as bears to the whole of the capital gain the`
  line `same proportion as the cost of acquisition of the long-term specified asset bears to the whole of the`
  line `capital gain, shall not be charged under section 45:`
  line `Provided that the investment made on or after the 1st day of April, 2016, in the long-term specified`
  line `asset by an assessee during any financial year does not exceed fifty lakh rupees:`
  line `Provided further that the investment made by an assessee in the long-term specified asset, from`
  line `capital gains arising from the transfer of one or more original assets, during the financial year in which`
  line `the original asset or assets are transferred and in the subsequent financial year does not exceed fifty lakh`
  line rupees.
  line `( 2 ) Where the long-term specified asset is transferred by the assessee at any time within a period of`
  line `three years from the date of its acquisition, the amount of capital gains arising from the transfer of the`
  line `original asset not charged under section 45 on the basis of the cost of such long-term specified asset as`
  line `provided in clause ( a ) or, as the case may be, clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to be the`
  line `income chargeable und er the head “Capital gains” relating to long -term capital asset of the previous year`
  line `in which the long-term specified asset is transferred.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 32 (w.e.f 1-4-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_291_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_292:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-292
  sectionNo (292)
  orderNo 292
  title `Page 292`
  content obj_root_law_sections_292_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_292_footnotes
  sourcePage 292
obj_root_law_sections_292_content:
  string
  line 292
  line `Explanation 1. — In a case where the original asset is transferred and the assessee invests the whole or`
  line `any part of the capital gain received or accrued as a result of transfer of the original asset in any long-term`
  line `specified asset and such assessee takes any loan or advance on the security of such specified asset, he`
  line `shall be deemed to have transferred such specified asset on the date on which such loan or advance is`
  line taken.
  line `Explanation 2. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “cost”, in relation to any long -term specified asset, means the amount invested in such`
  line `specified asset out of capital gains received or accruing as a result of the transfer of the original asset;`
  line `( b ) “long - term specified asset” means a unit or units, issued before the 1st day of April, 2019, of`
  line `such fund as may be notified by the Central Government in this behalf.]`
  line `1 [ 54F. Capital gain on transfer of certain capital assets not to be charged in case of investment`
  line `in residential house. — ( 1 ) 2 [Subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 4 ), where, in the case of an assessee`
  line `being an individual or a Hindu undivided family, the capital gain arises from the transfer of any long-term`
  line `capital asset, not being a residential house (hereafter in this section referred to as the original asset), and`
  line `the assessee has, within a period of one year before or 3 [two years] after the date on which the transfer`
  line `took place purchased, or has within a period of three years after that date 4 [constructed, one residential`
  line `house in India] (hereafter in this section referred to as the new asset), the capital gain shall be dealt with`
  line `in accordance with the following provisions of this section, that is to say, —`
  line `( a ) if the cost of the new asset is not less than the net consideration in respect of the original asset,`
  line `the whole of such capital gain shall not be charged under section 45;`
  line `( b ) if the cost of the new asset is less than the net consideration in respect of the original asset, so`
  line `much of the capital gain as bears to the whole of the capital gain the same proportion as the cost of`
  line `the new asset bears to the net consideration, shall not be charged under section 45:`
  line `5 [Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply where —`
  line `( a ) theassessee, —`
  line `( i ) owns more than one residential house, other than the new asset, on the date of transfer`
  line `of the original asset; or`
  line `( ii ) purchases any residential house, other than the new asset, within a period of one year`
  line `after the date of transfer of the original asset; or`
  line `( iii ) constructs any residential house, other than the new asset, within a period of three`
  line `years after the date of transfer of the original asset; and`
  line `( b ) the income from such residential house, other than the one residential house owned on the`
  line `date of transfer of the original asset, is chargeable under the head “Income from house property”.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `6 * * * * *`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 1982, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-1983).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 23, for “Where, in the case of an assesse being an individual” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f 1-4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 24, for “constructed, a residential house” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2015).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 28, for the proviso (w.e.f 1-4-2001).`
  line `6. Clause ( i ) omitted by Act 11 of 1987, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_292_footnotes:
