obj_root_law_sections_294:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-294
  sectionNo (294)
  orderNo 294
  title `Page 294`
  content obj_root_law_sections_294_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_294_footnotes
  sourcePage 294
obj_root_law_sections_294_content:
  string
  line 294
  line `( ii ) the assessee shall be entitled to withdraw the unutilised amount in accordance with the`
  line `scheme aforesaid.`
  line `1 * * * * *]`
  line `2 [54G. Exemption of capital gains on transfer of assets in cases of shifting of industrial`
  line `undertaking from urban area. — ( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ), where the capital gain`
  line `arises from the transfer of a capital asset, being machinery or plant or building or land or any rights in`
  line `building or land used for the purposes of the business of an industrial undertaking situate in an urban area,`
  line `effected in the course of, or in consequence of, the shifting of such industrial undertaking (hereafter in`
  line `this section referred to as the original asset) to any area (other than an urban area) and the assessee has`
  line `within a period of one year before or three years after the date on which the transfer took place, —`
  line `( a ) purchased new machinery or plant for the purposes of business of the industrial undertaking in`
  line `the area to which the said undertaking is shifted;`
  line `( b ) acquired building or land or constructed building for the purposes of his business in the said`
  line area;
  line `( c ) shifted the original asset and transferred the establishment of such undertaking to such area;`
  line and
  line `( d ) incurred expenses on such other purpose as may be specified in a scheme framed by the`
  line `Central Government for the purposes of this section,`
  line `then, instead of the capital gain being charged to income-tax as income of the previous year in which the`
  line `transfer took place, it shall be dealt with in accordance with the following provisions of this section, that`
  line `is to say, —`
  line `( i ) if the amount of the capital gain is greater than the cost and expenses incurred in relation to all`
  line `or any of the purposes mentioned in clauses ( a ) to ( d ) (such cost and expenses being hereafter in this`
  line `section referred to as the new asset), the difference between the amount of the capital gain and the`
  line `cost of the new asset shall be charged under section 45 as the income of the previous year; and for`
  line `the purpose of computing in respect of the new asset any capital gain arising from its transfer within a`
  line `period of three years of its being purchased, acquired, constructed or transferred, as the case may be,`
  line `the cost shall be nil; or`
  line `( ii ) if the amount of the capital gain is equal to, or less than, the cost of the new asset, the capital`
  line `gain shall not be charged under section 45; and for the purpose of computing in respect of the new`
  line `asset any capital gain arising from its transfer within a period of three years of its being purchased,`
  line `acquired, constructed or transferred, as the case may be, the cost shall be reduced by the amount of`
  line `the capital gain.`
  line `Explanation. — In this sub- section, “urban area” means any such area within the limits of a municipal`
  line `corporation or municipality as the Central Government may, having regard to the population,`
  line `concentration of industries, need for proper planning of the area and other relevant factors, by general or`
  line `special order, declare to be an urban area for the purposes of this sub-section.`
  line `1. The Explanation omitted by 18 of 1992, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_294_footnotes:
