  line
obj_root_law_sections_295:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-295
  sectionNo (295)
  orderNo 295
  title `Page 295`
  content obj_root_law_sections_295_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_295_footnotes
  sourcePage 295
obj_root_law_sections_295_content:
  string
  line 295
  line `( 2 ) The amount of capital gain which is not appropriated by the assessee towards the cost and`
  line `expenses incurred in relation to all or any of the purposes mentioned in clauses ( a ) to ( d ) of sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) within one year before the date on which the transfer of the original asset took place, or which is not`
  line `utilised by him for all or any of the purposes aforesaid before the date of furnishing the return of income`
  line `under section 139, shall be deposited by him before furnishing such return [such deposit being made in`
  line `any case not later than the due date applicable in the case of the assessee for furnishing the return of`
  line `income under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139] in an account in any such bank or institution as may be`
  line `specified in, and utilised in accordance with, any scheme which the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, frame in this behalf and such return shall be accompanied by proof of`
  line `such deposit; and, for the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), the amount, if any, already utilised by the assessee`
  line `for all or any of the purposes aforesaid together with the amount, so deposited shall be deemed to be the`
  line `cost of the new asset:`
  line `Provided that if the amount deposited under this sub-section is not utilised wholly or partly for all or`
  line `any of the purposes mentioned in clauses (a) to (d) of sub-section ( 1 ) within the period specified in that`
  line `sub-section, then, —`
  line `( i ) the amount not so utilised shall be charged under section 45 as the income of the previous year`
  line `in which the period of three years from the date of the transfer of the original asset expires; and`
  line `( ii ) theassessee shall be entitled to withdraw such amount in accordance with the scheme`
  line aforesaid.
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `2 [54GA. Exemption of capital gains on transfer of assets in cases of shifting of industrial`
  line `undertaking from urban area to any Special Economic Zone. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 54G, where the capital gain arises from the transfer of a capital asset, being`
  line `machinery or plant or building or land or any rights in building or land used for the purposes of the`
  line `business of an industrial undertaking situate in an urban area, effected in the course of, or in consequence`
  line `of the shifting of such industrial undertaking to any Special Economic Zone, whether developed in any`
  line `urban area or any other area and the assessee has within a period of one year before or three years after`
  line `the date on which the transfer took place, —`
  line `( a ) purchased machinery or plant for the purposes of business of the industrial undertaking in the`
  line `Special Economic Zone to which the said undertaking is shifted;`
  line `( b ) acquired building or land or constructed building for the purposes of his business in the`
  line `Special Economic Zone;`
  line `( c ) shifted the original asset and transferred the establishment of such undertaking to the Special`
  line `Economic Zone; and`
  line `( d ) incurred expenses on such other purposes as may be specified in a scheme framed by the`
  line `Central Government for the purposes of this section,`
  line `1. The Explanation omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 28 of 2005, s. 27 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 10-2-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_295_footnotes:
  string
  line
