obj_root_law_sections_296_content:
  string
  line 296
  line `then, instead of the capital gain being charged to income-tax as income of the previous year in which the`
  line `transfer took place, it shall, subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ), be dealt with in accordance with`
  line `the following provisions of this section, that is to say, —`
  line `( i ) if the amount of the capital gain is greater than the cost and expenses incurred in relation to all`
  line `or any of the purposes mentioned in clauses ( a ) to ( d ) (such cost and expenses being hereafter in this`
  line `section referred to as the new asset), the difference between the amount of the capital gain and the`
  line `cost of the new asset shall be charged under section 45 as the income of the previous year; and for the`
  line `purpose of computing in respect of the new asset any capital gain arising from its transfer within a`
  line `period of three years of its being purchased, acquired, constructed or transferred, as the case may be,`
  line `the cost shall be Nil; or`
  line `( ii ) if the amount of the capital gain is equal to, or less than, the cost of the new asset, the capital`
  line `gain shall not be charged under section 45, and for the purpose of computing in respect of the new`
  line `asset any capital gain arising from its transfer within a period of three years of its being purchased,`
  line `acquired, constructed or transferred, as the case may be, the cost shall be reduced by the amount of`
  line `the capital gain.`
  line `Explanation. — In this sub-section, —`
  line `( a ) “Special Economic Zone” shall have the meaning assigned to i t in clause ( za ) of the`
  line `Special Economic Zones Act, 2005;`
  line `( b ) “urban area” means any such area within the limits of a municipal corporation or`
  line `municipality as the Central Government may, having regard to the population, concentration of`
  line `industries, need for proper planning of the area and other relevant factors, by general or special`
  line `order, declare to be an urban area for the purposes of this sub-section.`
  line `( 2 ) The amount of capital gain which is not appropriated by the assessee towards the cost and`
  line `expenses incurred in relation to all or any of the purposes mentioned in clauses ( a ) to ( d ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) within one year before the date on which the transfer of the original asset took place, or`
  line `which is not utilised by him for all or any of the purposes aforesaid before the date of furnishing the`
  line `return of income under section 139, shall be deposited by him before furnishing such return [such deposit`
  line `being made in any case not later than the due date applicable in the case of the assessee for furnishing the`
  line `return of income under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139] in an account in any such bank or institution as`
  line `may be specified in, and utilised in accordance with, any scheme which the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, frame in this behalf and such return shall be accompanied by proof of such deposit; and, for`
  line `the purposes of sub-section (1), the amount, if any, already utilised by the assessee for all or any of the`
  line `aforesaid purposes together with the amount so deposited shall be deemed to be the cost of the new asset:`
  line `Provided that if the amount deposited under this sub-section is not utilised wholly or partly for all or`
  line `any of the purposes mentioned in clauses (a) to (d) of sub-section (1) within the period specified in that`
  line `sub-section, then, —`
  line `( i ) the amount not so utilised shall be charged under section 45 as the income of the previous year`
  line `in which the period of three years from the date of the transfer of the original asset expires; and`
  line `( ii ) the assessee shall be entitled to withdraw such amount in accordance with the scheme`
  line aforesaid.]
obj_root_law_sections_296_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_297:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-297
  sectionNo (297)
  orderNo 297
  title `Page 297`
  content obj_root_law_sections_297_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_297_footnotes
  sourcePage 297
obj_root_law_sections_297_content:
  string
  line 297
  line `1 [ 54GB. Capital gain on transfer of residential property not to be charged in certain`
  line `cases. — ( 1 ) Where, —`
  line `( i ) the capital gain arises from the transfer of a long-term capital asset, being a residential`
  line `property (a house or a plot of land), owned by the eligible assessee (herein referred to as the`
  line `assessee); and`
  line `( ii ) the assessee, before the due date of furnishing of return of income under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 139, utilises the net consideration for subscription in the equity shares of an eligible`
  line `company (herein referred to as the company); and`
  line `( iii ) the company has, within one year from the date of subscription in equity shares by the`
  line `assessee, utilised this amount for purchase of new asset,`
  line `then, instead of the capital gain being charged to income-tax as the income of the previous year in which`
  line `the transfer takes place, it shall be dealt with in accordance with the following provisions of this section,`
  line `that is to say, —`
  line `( a ) if the amount of the net consideration is greater than the cost of the new asset, then, so much`
  line `of the capital gain as it bears to the whole of the capital gain the same proportion as the cost of the`
  line `new asset bears to the net consideration, shall not be charged under section 45 as the income of the`
  line `previous year; or`
  line `( b ) if the amount of the net consideration is equal to or less than the cost of the new asset, the`
  line `capital gain shall not be charged under section 45 as the income of the previous year.`
  line `( 2 ) The amount of the net consideration, which has been received by the company for issue of shares`
  line `to the assessee, to the extent it is not utilised by the company for the purchase of the new asset before the`
  line `due date of furnishing of the return of income by the assessee under section 139, shall be deposited by the`
  line `company, before the said due date in an account in any such bank or institution as may be specified and`
  line `shall be utilised in accordance with any scheme which the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, frame in this behalf and the return furnished by the assessee shall be accompanied by`
  line `proof of such deposit having been made.`
  line `( 3 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), the amount, if any, already utilised by the company for the`
  line `purchase of the new asset together with the amount deposited under sub-section ( 2 ) shall be deemed to be`
  line `the cost of the new asset:`
  line `Provided that if the amount so deposited is not utilised, wholly or partly, for the purchase of the new`
  line `asset within the period specified in sub-section ( 1 ), then, —`
  line `( i ) the amount by which —`
  line `( a ) the amount of capital gain arising from the transfer of the residential property not charged`
  line `under section 45 on the basis of the cost of the new asset as provided in sub-section ( 1 ),`
  line `exceeds —`
  line `( b ) the amount that would not have been so charged had the amount actually utilised for the`
  line `purchase of the new asset within the period specified in sub-section ( 1 )been the cost of the new`
  line asset,
  line `shall be charged under section 45 as income of the assessee for the previous year in which the period`
  line `of one year from the date of the subscription in equity shares by the assessee expires; and`
  line `( ii ) the company shall be entitled to withdraw such amount in accordance with the scheme.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_297_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_298:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-298
  sectionNo (298)
  orderNo 298
  title `Page 298`
  content obj_root_law_sections_298_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_298_footnotes
  sourcePage 298
obj_root_law_sections_298_content:
  string
  line 298
  line `( 4 ) If the equity shares of the company or the new asset acquired by the company are sold or`
  line `otherwise transferred within a period of five years from the date of their acquisition, the amount of capital`
  line `gain arising from the transfer of the residential property not charged under section 45 as provided in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to be the income of the assessee chargeable under the head “Capital`
  line `gains” of the previous year in which such equity shares or such new asset are sold or otherwise`
  line `transferred, in addition to taxability of gains, arising on account of transfer of shares or of the new asset,`
  line `in the hands of the assessee or the company, as the case may be.`
  line `( 5 ) The provisions of this section shall not apply to any transfer of residential property made after the`
  line `31st day of March, 2017.`
  line `1 [Provided that in case of an investment in eligible start-up, the provisions of this sub-section shall`
  line `have the effect as if for the figures, letters and words “31st day of March, 2017”, the figures, letters and`
  line `words “31st day of March, 2019” had been su bstituted.]`
  line `( 6 ) For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “eligible assessee” means an individual or a Hindu undivided family;`
  line `( b ) “eligible company” means a company which fulfils the following conditions, namely:—`
  line `( i ) it is a company incorporated in India during the period from the 1st day of April of the`
  line `previous year relevant to the assessment year in which the capital gain arises to the due date of`
  line `furnishing of return of income under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139 by the assessee;`
  line `( ii ) it is engaged in the business of manufacture of an article or a thing 1 [ or in an eligible`
  line `business; ]`
  line `( iii ) it is a company in which the assessee has more than fifty per cent. share capital or more`
  line `than fifty per cent. voting rights after the subscription in shares by the assessee; and`
  line `( iv ) it is a company which qualifies to be a small or medium enterprise under the Micro,`
  line `Small and Medium Enterprises Act, 2006 (27 of 2006) 1 [ or is an eligible start-up ];`
  line `1 [( ba ) “eligible start - up” and “eligible business” shall have the meani ngs respectively assigned to`
  line `them in Explanation below sub-section ( 4) of section 80-IAC;]`
  line `( c ) “net consideration” shall have the meaning assigned to it in the Explanation to section 54F;`
  line `( d ) “new asset” means new plant and machinery but does not include—`
  line `( i ) any machinery or plant which, before its installation by the assessee, was used either`
  line `within or outside India by any other person;`
  line `( ii ) any machinery or plant installed in any office premises or any residential accommodation,`
  line `including accommodation in the nature of a guest-house;`
  line `( iii ) any office appliances including computers or computer software;`
  line `( iv ) any vehicle; or`
  line `( v ) any machinery or plant, the whole of the actual cost of which is allowed as a deduction`
  line `(whether by way of depreciation or otherwise) in computing the income chargeable under the`
  line `head “Profits and gains of business or profession” of any previous year.]`
  line `1. The proviso ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 33 (1-4-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_298_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_299:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-299
  sectionNo (299)
