obj_root_law_sections_300_content:
  string
  line 300
  line `( 2 ) 1 [For the purposes of sections 48 and 49, “cost of acquisition”,—`
  line `2 [( a ) in relation to a capital asset, being goodwill of a business 3 [or a trade mark or brand name`
  line `associated with a business] 4 [or a right to manufacture, produce or process any article or thing] 5 [or`
  line `right to carry on any business 6 [or profession]], tenancy rights, stage carriage permits or loom`
  line `hours, —`
  line `( i ) in the case of acquisition of such asset by the assessee by purchase from a previous`
  line `owner, means the amount of the purchase price; and`
  line `( ii ) in any other case [not being a case falling under sub-clauses ( i ) to ( iv ) of sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 49], shall be taken to be nil;`
  line `( aa ) 7 [in a case where, by virtue of holding a capital asset, being a share or any other security,`
  line `within the meaning of clause ( h ) of section 2 of the Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of`
  line `1956) (hereafter in this clause referred to as the financial asset), the assessee —`
  line `( A ) becomes entitled to subscribe to any additional financial asset; or`
  line `( B ) is allotted any additional financial asset without any payment,`
  line `then, subject to the provisions of sub-clauses ( i ) and ( ii ) of clause ( b ), —`
  line `( i ) in relation to the original financial asset, on the basis of which the assessee becomes`
  line `entitled to any additional financial asset, means the amount actually paid for acquiring the`
  line `original financial asset;`
  line `( ii ) in relation to any right to renounce the said entitlement to subscribe to the financial asset,`
  line `when such right is renounced by the assessee in favour of any person, shall be taken to be nil in`
  line `the case of such assessee;`
  line `( iii ) in relation to the financial asset, to which the assessee has subscribed on the basis of the`
  line `said entitlement, means the amount actually paid by him for acquiring such asset;`
  line `8 [( iiia ) in relation to the financial asset allotted to the assessee without any payment and on`
  line `the basis of holding of any other financial asset, shall be taken to be nil in the case of such`
  line `assessee;] and`
  line `( iv ) in relation to any financial asset purchased by any person in whose favour the right to`
  line `subscribe to such asset has been renounced, means the aggregate of the amount of the purchase`
  line `price paid by him to the person renouncing such right and the amount paid by him to the`
  line `company or institution, as the case may be, for acquiring such financial asset;]`
  line `9 [( ab ) in relation to a capital asset, being equity share or shares allotted to a shareholder of a`
  line `recognised stock exchange in India under a scheme for 10 [demutualisation or corporatisation]`
  line `approved by the Securities and Exchange Board of India established under section 3 of the Securities`
  line `and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992), shall be the cost of acquisition of his original`
  line `membership of the exchange:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 25, for the “For the purposes of sections 48 and 49, “cost of acquisition”, in relation to a`
  line `capital asset, — ” (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 18, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
  line `3. Ins. by 14 of 2001, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `5. Ins. by 20 of 2002, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 14, for “in a case where, “and ending with “sub -clauses ( i ) and ( ii ) of clause ( b )”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1996).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-1996).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 31, for “corporatisation” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2004).`
