obj_root_law_sections_302_content:
  string
  line 302
  line `1 [Provided that the cost of a capital asset, being trading or clearing rights of the recognised`
  line `stock exchange acquired by a shareholder who has been allotted equity share or shares under such`
  line `scheme of demutualisation or corporatisation, shall be deemed to be nil;]`
  line `( b ) in relation to any other capital asset, — ]`
  line `( i ) where the capital asset became the property of the assessee before the 2 [1st day of`
  line `April, 2001], means the cost of acquisition of the asset to the assessee or the fairmarket value of`
  line `the asset on the 2 [1st day of April, 2001], at the option of the assessee;`
  line `( ii ) where the capital asset became the property of the assessee by any of the modes specified`
  line `in 3 [sub-section ( 1 ) of section 49], and the capital asset became the property of the previous`
  line `owner before the 2 [1st day of April, 2001], means the cost of the capital asset to the previous`
  line `owner or the fairmarket value of the asset on the 2 [1st day of April, 2001], at the option of the`
  line assessee;
  line `( iii ) where the capital asset became the property of the assessee on the distribution of the`
  line `capital assets of a company on itsliquidation and the assessee has been assessed to income-tax`
  line `under the head “Capital gains” in respect of that asset under section 46, means the fairmarket`
  line `value of the asset on the date of distribution;`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `5 [( v ) where the capital asset, being a share or a stock of a company, became the property of`
  line `the assessee on —`
  line `( a ) the consolidation and division of all or any of the sharecapital of the company into`
  line `shares of larger amount than its existing shares,`
  line `( b ) the conversion of any shares of the company into stock,`
  line `( c ) the re-conversion of any stock of the company into shares,`
  line `( d ) the sub-division of any of the shares of the company into shares of smaller amount, or`
  line `( e ) the conversion of one kind of shares of the company into another kind,`
  line `means the cost of acquisition of the asset calculated with reference to the cost of acquisition of the`
  line `shares or stock from which such asset is derived.]`
  line `( 3 ) Where the cost for which the previous owner acquired the property cannot be ascertained, the cost`
  line `of acquisition to the previous owner means the fair market value on the date on which the capital asset`
  line `became the property of the previous owner.`
  line `6 [55A. Reference to Valuation Officer. — With a view to ascertaining the fair market value of a`
  line `capital asset for the purposes of this Chapter, the 7 [Assessing Officer] may refer the valuation of capital`
  line `asset to a Valuation Officer —`
  line `( a ) in a case where the value of the asset as claimed by the assessee is in accordance with the`
  line `estimate made by a registered valuer, if the 7 [Assessing Officer] is of opinion that the value so`
  line `claimed 8 [is at variance with its fair market value];`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 28, for “1st day of April, 1981” (w.e.f. 1-4- 2018). Earlier “1st day of April, 1974” was`
  line `substituted by Act 23 of 1986, s. 13, for “1st day of January, 1964” (w.e.f. 1 -4- 1987) and later “1981” was substituted`
  line `by Act 18 of 1992, s. 34, for “1974” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1993).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 21, for “section 49” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1967).`
  line `4. Clause ( iv ) omitted by Act 13 of 1966, s. 14 (w.e.f 1-4-1967).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 5 of 1964, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-1964).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 45 of 1972, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-1-1973).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “I ncome- tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 20, for “is less than its fair market value” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
