  content obj_root_law_sections_303_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_303_footnotes
  sourcePage 303
obj_root_law_sections_303_content:
  string
  line 303
  line `( b ) in any other case, if the 1 [Assessing Officer] is of opinion —`
  line `( i ) that the fair market value of the asset exceeds the value of the asset as claimed by the`
  line `assessee by more than such percentage of the value of the asset as so claimed or by more than`
  line `such amountas may be prescribed in this behalf; or`
  line `( ii ) that having regard to the nature of the asset and other relevant circumstances, it is`
  line `necessary so to do,`
  line `and where any such reference is made, the provisions of sub-sections ( 2 ), ( 3 ), ( 4 ), ( 5 ) and ( 6 ) of section`
  line `16A, clauses ( ha ) and ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) and sub-sections ( 3A ) and ( 4 ) of section 23, sub-section ( 5 ) of`
  line `section 24, section 34AA, section 35 and section 37 of the Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957), shall with`
  line `the necessary modifications, apply in relation to such reference as they apply in relation to a reference`
  line `made by the 1 [Assessing Officer] under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 16A of that Act.`
  line `Explanation. —In this section, “Valuation Officer” has the same meani ng, as in clause ( r ) of section 2`
  line `of the Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957).]`
  line `56. Income from other sources. — ( 1 ) Income of every kind which is not to be excluded from the`
  line `total income under this Act shall be chargeable to income- tax under the head “Income from other`
  line `sources”, if it is not chargeable to income -tax under any of the heads specified in section 14, items A to E.`
  line `( 2 ) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ), the`
  line `following incomes, shall be chargeable to income- tax under the head “Income from other sources”,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( i ) dividends;`
  line `2 [( ia ) income referred to in sub-clause ( viii ) of clause ( 24 ) of section 2;]`
  line `3 [( ib ) income referred to in sub-clause ( ix ) of clause ( 24 ) of section 2;]`
  line `4 [( ic ) income referred to in sub-clause ( x ) of clause ( 24 ) of section 2, if such income is not`
  line `chargeable to income- tax under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession”;]`
  line `5 [( id ) income by way of interest on securities, if the income is not chargeable to income-tax under`
  line `the head “Profits and gains of business or profession”;]`
  line `( ii ) income from machinery, plant or furniture belonging to the assessee and let on hire, if the`
  line `income is not chargeable to income- tax under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession”;`
  line `( iii ) where an assessee lets on hire machinery, plant or furniture belonging to him and also`
  line `buildings, and the letting of the buildings is inseparable from the letting of the said machinery, plant`
  line `or furniture, the income from such letting, if it is not chargeable to income- tax under the head “Profits`
  line `and gains of business or profession”;`
  line `6 [( iv ) income referred to in sub-clause ( xi ) of clause ( 24 ) of section 2, if such income is not`
  line `chargeable to income- tax under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession” or under the`
  line `head “Salaries”;]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 26 of 1988, s.18 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-10-1996).`
