obj_root_law_sections_304_content:
  string
  line 304
  line `1 [( v ) where any sum of money exceeding twenty-five thousand rupees is received without`
  line `consideration by an individual or a Hindu undivided family from any person on or after the 1st day of`
  line `September, 2004 2 [but before the 1st day of April, 2006], the whole of such sum:`
  line `Provided that this clause shall not apply to any sum of money received —`
  line `( a ) from any relative; or`
  line `( b ) on the occasion of the marriage of the individual; or`
  line `( c ) under a will or by way of inheritance; or`
  line `( d ) in contemplation of death of the payer; or`
  line `3 [( e ) from any local authority as defined in the Explanation to clause ( 20 ) of section 10; or`
  line `( f ) from any fund or foundation or university or other educational institution or hospital or`
  line `other medical institution or any trust or institution referred to in clause ( 23C ) of section 10; or`
  line `( g ) from any trust or institution registered under section 12AA.]`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, “relative” means—`
  line `( i ) spouse of the individual;`
  line `( ii ) brother or sister of the individual;`
  line `( iii ) brother or sister of the spouse of the individual;`
  line `( iv ) brother or sister of either of the parents of the individual;`
  line `( v ) any lineal ascendant or descendant of the individual;`
  line `( vi ) any lineal ascendant or descendant of the spouse of the individual;`
  line `( vii ) spouse of the person referred to in clauses ( ii ) to ( vi );]`
  line `4 [( vi ) where any sum of money, the aggregate value of which exceeds fifty thousand rupees,`
  line `is received without consideration, by an individual or a Hindu undivided family, in any previous`
  line `year from any person or persons on or after the 1st day of April, 2006 5 [but before the 1st day of`
  line `October, 2009], the whole of the aggregate value of such sum:`
  line `Provided that this clause shall not apply to any sum of money received —`
  line `( a ) from any relative; or`
  line `( b ) on the occasion of the marriage of the individual; or`
  line `( c ) under a will or by way of inheritance; or`
  line `( d ) in contemplation of death of the payer; or`
  line `( e ) from any local authority as defined in the Explanation to clause ( 20 ) of section 10; or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-10-2009).`
