  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_305_footnotes
  sourcePage 305
obj_root_law_sections_305_content:
  string
  line 305
  line `( f ) from any fund or foundation or university or other educational institution or hospital`
  line `or other medical institution or any trust or institution referred to in clause ( 23C ) of`
  line `section 10; or`
  line `( g ) from any trust or institution registered under section 12AA.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purpos es of this clause, “relative” means—`
  line `( i ) spouse of the individual;`
  line `( ii ) brother or sister of the individual;`
  line `( iii ) brother or sister of the spouse of the individual;`
  line `( iv ) brother or sister of either of the parents of the individual;`
  line `( v ) any lineal ascendant or descendant of the individual;`
  line `( vi ) any lineal ascendant or descendant of the spouse of the individual;`
  line `( vii ) spouse of the person referred to in clauses ( ii ) to ( vi );]`
  line `1 [( vii ) where an individual or a Hindu undivided family receives, in any previous year, from`
  line `any person or persons on or after the 1st day of October, 2009 2 [but before the 1st day of April,`
  line `2017], —`
  line `( a ) any sum of money, without consideration, the aggregate value of which exceeds fifty`
  line `thousand rupees, the whole of the aggregate value of such sum;`
  line `3 [( b ) any immovable property, —`
  line `( i ) without consideration, the stamp duty value of which exceeds fifty thousand`
  line `rupees, the stamp duty value of such property;`
  line `( ii ) for a consideration which is less than the stamp duty value of the property by an`
  line `amount exceeding fifty thousand rupees, the stamp duty value of such property as`
  line `exceeds such consideration:`
  line `Provided that where the date of the agreement fixing the amount of consideration for the`
  line `transfer of immovable property and the date of registration are not the same, the stamp duty`
  line `value on the date of the agreement may be taken for the purposes of this sub-clause:`
  line `Provided further that the said proviso shall apply only in a case where the amount of`
  line `consideration referred to therein, or a part thereof, has been paid by any mode other than cash`
  line `on or before the date of the agreement for the transfer of such immovable property;]`
  line `( c ) any property, other than immovable property, —`
  line `( i ) without consideration, the aggregate fair market value of which exceeds fifty`
  line `thousand rupees, the whole of the aggregate fair market value of such property;`
  line `( ii ) for a consideration which is less than the aggregate fair market value of the`
  line `property by an amount exceeding fifty thousand rupees, the aggregate fair market value`
  line `of such property as exceeds such consideration:`
  line `Provided that where the stamp duty value of immovable property as referred to in`
  line `sub-clause ( b ) is disputed by the assessee on grounds mentioned in sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 50C, the Assessing Officer may refer the valuation of such property to a`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-10-2009).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `3.. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
