obj_root_law_sections_306_content:
  string
  line 306
  line `Valuation Officer, and the provisions of section 50C and sub-section ( 15 ) of section`
  line `155 shall, as far as may be, apply in relation to the stamp duty value of such property for`
  line `the purpose of sub-clause ( b ) as they apply for valuation of capital asset under those`
  line `sections:`
  line `Provided further that this clause shall not apply to any sum of money or any property`
  line `received —`
  line `( a ) from any relative; or`
  line `( b ) on the occasion of the marriage of the individual; or`
  line `( c ) under a will or by way of inheritance; or`
  line `( d ) in contemplation of death of the payer or donor, as the case may be; or`
  line `( e ) from any local authority as defined in the Explanation to clause ( 20 ) of section 10; or`
  line `( f ) from any fund or foundation or university or other educational institution or hospital`
  line `or other medical institution or any trust or institution referred to in clause ( 23C ) ofsection 10;`
  line or
  line `( g ) from any trust or institution registered under 1 [section 12AA; or]`
  line `2 [( h ) by way of transaction not regarded as transfer under clause ( vicb ) or clause ( vid ) or`
  line `clause ( vii ) of section 47.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( a ) “assessable” shall have the meaning assigned to it in the Explanation 2 to sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 50C;`
  line `( b ) “fair market value” of a property, other than an immovable property, means the value`
  line `determined in accordance with the method as may be prescribed;`
  line `( c ) “jewellery” shall have the meaning assigned to it in the Explanation to sub-clause ( ii ) of`
  line `clause ( 14 ) of section 2;`
  line `( d ) “property” 3 [means the following capital asset of the assessee, namely: — ]`
  line `( i ) immovable property being land or building or both;`
  line `( ii ) shares and securities;`
  line `( iii ) jewellery;`
  line `( iv ) archaeological collections;`
  line `( v ) drawings;`
  line `( vi ) paintings;`
  line `( vii ) sculptures; 4 ***`
  line `( viii ) any work of art; 5 [or]`
  line `5 [( ix ) bullion;]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 35, for “section 12AA” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 35, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 21, for “means—” (w.r.e.f. 1 -10-2009).`
  line `4. The word “or” omitted by s. 21, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2010).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 21, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2010).`
