  content obj_root_law_sections_308_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_308_footnotes
  sourcePage 308
obj_root_law_sections_308_content:
  string
  line 308
  line `1 [( viib ) where a company, not being a company in which the public are substantially`
  line `interested, receives, in any previous year, from any person being a resident, any consideration for`
  line `issue of shares that exceeds the face value of such shares, the aggregate consideration received for`
  line `such shares as exceeds the fair market value of the shares:`
  line `Provided that this clause shall not apply where the consideration for issue of shares is`
  line `received —`
  line `( i ) by a venture capital undertaking from a venture capital company or a venture capital`
  line `fund; or`
  line `( ii ) by a company from a class or classes of persons as may be notified by the Central`
  line `Government in this behalf.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( a ) the fair market value of the shares shall be the value —`
  line `( i ) as may be determined in accordance with such method as may be prescribed; or`
  line `( ii ) as may be substantiated by the company to the satisfaction of the Assessing Officer, based`
  line `on the value, on the date of issue of shares, of its assets, including intangible assets being`
  line `goodwill, know-how, patents, copyrights, trademarks, licences, franchises or any other business`
  line `or commercial rights of similar nature,`
  line `whichever is higher;`
  line `( b ) “venture capital company”, “venture capital fund” and “venture capital undertaking” shall`
  line `have the meanings respectively assigned to them in clause ( a ), clause ( b ) and clause ( c )`
  line `of 2 [ Explanation ] to clause ( 23FB ) of section 10;]`
  line `3 [( viii ) income by way of interest received on compensation or on enhanced compensation`
  line `referred to in clause ( b ) of section 145A;]`
  line `4 [( ix ) any sum of money received as an advance or otherwise in the course of negotiations for`
  line `transfer of a capital asset, if, —`
  line `( a ) such sum is forfeited; and`
  line `( b ) the negotiations do not result in transfer of such capital asset.]`
  line `5 [( x ) where any person receives, in any previous year, from any person or persons on or after`
  line `the 1st day of April, 2017, —`
  line `( a ) any sum of money, without consideration, the aggregate value of which exceeds fifty`
  line `thousand rupees, the whole of the aggregate value of such sum;`
  line `( b ) any immovable property, —`
  line `( A ) without consideration, the stamp duty value of which exceeds fifty thousand`
  line `rupees, the stamp duty value of such property;`
  line `6 [( B ) for a consideration, the stamp duty value of such property as exceeds such`
  line `consideration, if the amount of such excess is more than the higher of the following`
  line `amounts, namely: ––`
  line `( i ) the amount of fifty thousand rupees; and`
  line `( ii ) the amount equal to five per cent. of the consideration:]`
  line `Provided that where the date of agreement fixing the amount of consideration for`
  line `the transfer of immovable property and the date of registration are not the same, the`
  line `stamp duty value on the date of agreement may be taken for the purposes of this`
  line `sub-clause:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 11, for “ Explanation 1 ” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2014).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017)`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 23, for item ( B ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_308_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_309:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-309
  sectionNo (309)
  orderNo 309
  title `Page 309`
  content obj_root_law_sections_309_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_309_footnotes
  sourcePage 309
obj_root_law_sections_309_content:
  string
  line 309
  line `Provided further that the provisions of the first proviso shall apply only in a case`
  line `where the amount of consideration referred to therein, or a part thereof, has been paid by`
  line `way of an account payee cheque or an account payee bank draft or by use of electronic`
  line `clearing system through a bank account, on or before the date of agreement for transfer of`
  line `such immovable property:`
  line `Provided also that where the stamp duty value of immovable property is disputed by`
  line `the assessee on grounds mentioned in sub-section ( 2 ) of section 50C, the Assessing`
  line `Officer may refer the valuation of such property to a Valuation Officer, and the`
  line `provisions of section 50C and sub-section ( 15 ) of section 155 shall, as far as may be,`
  line `apply in relation to the stamp duty value of such property for the purpose of this`
  line `sub-clause as they apply for valuation of capital asset under those sections;`
  line `( c ) any property, other than immovable property, —`
  line `( A ) without consideration, the aggregate fair market value of which exceeds fifty`
  line `thousand rupees, the whole of the aggregate fair market value of such property;`
  line `( B ) for a consideration which is less than the aggregate fair market value of the`
  line `property by an amount exceeding fifty thousand rupees, the aggregate fair market value`
  line `of such property as exceeds such consideration:`
  line `Provided that this clause shall not apply to any sum of money or any property`
  line `received —`
  line `( I ) from any relative; or`
  line `( II ) on the occasion of the marriage of the individual; or`
  line `( III ) under a will or by way of inheritance; or`
  line `( IV ) in contemplation of death of the payer or donor, as the case may be; or`
  line `( V ) from any local authority as defined in the Explanation to clause ( 20 ) of`
  line `section 10; or`
  line `( VI ) from any fund or foundation or university or other educational institution or`
  line `hospital or other medical institution or any trust or institution referred to in`
  line `clause ( 23C ) of section 10; or`
  line `( VII ) from or by any trust or institution registered under section 12A or`
  line `section 12AA; or`
  line `( VIII ) by any fund or trust or institution or any university or other educational`
  line `institution or any hospital or other medical institution referred to in sub-clause ( iv ) or`
  line `sub-clause ( v ) or sub-clause ( vi ) or sub-clause ( via ) of clause ( 23C ) of section 10; or`
  line `( IX ) by way of transaction not regarded as transfer under clause ( i ) or 1 [clause`
  line `( iv ) or clause ( v ) or] clause ( vi ) or clause ( via ) or clause ( viaa ) or clause ( vib ) or`
  line `clause ( vic ) or clause ( vica ) or clause ( vicb ) or clause ( vid ) or clause ( vii ) of section`
  line `47; or`
  line `( X ) from an individual by a trust created or established solely for the benefit of`
  line `relative of the individual.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, the expressions “assessable”, “fair market`
  line `value”, “jewellery”, “property”, “relative” and “stamp duty value” shall have the same`
  line `meanings as respectively assigned to them in the Explanation to clause ( vii ).]`
  line `2 [( xi ) any compensation or other payment, due to or received by any person, by whatever`
  line `name called, in connection with the termination of his employment or the modification of the`
  line `terms and conditions relating thereto.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_309_footnotes:
  string
