  title `Page 311`
  content obj_root_law_sections_311_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_311_footnotes
  sourcePage 311
obj_root_law_sections_311_content:
  string
  line 311
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `3 [( 1A ) The provisions of 4 [sub-clauses ( ia ) and ( iia )] of clause ( a ) of section 40 shall, so far as may`
  line `be, apply in computing the income chargeable under the head “Income from other sources” as they apply`
  line `in computing the income chargeable under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession”.]`
  line `5 [( 2 ) The provisions of section 40A shall, so far as may be, apply in computing the income chargeable`
  line `under the head “Income from other sources” as they apply in computing the income chargeable under the`
  line `head “Profits and gains of business or profession”.]`
  line `6 [( 3 ) In the case of an assessee, being a foreign company, the provisions of section 44D shall, so far`
  line `as may be, apply in computing the income ch argeable under the head “Income from other sources” as`
  line `they apply in computing the income chargeable under the head “Profits and gains of business or`
  line profession”.]
  line `7 [( 4 ) In the case of an assessee having income chargeable under the head “Income from other`
  line `sources”, no deduction in respect of any expenditure or allowance in connection with such income shall`
  line `be allowed under any provision of this Act in computing the income by way of any winnings from`
  line `lotteries, crossword puzzles, races including horse races, card games and other games of any sort or from`
  line `gambling or betting of any form or nature, whatsoever:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply in computing the income of an`
  line `assessee, being the owner of horses maintained by him for running in horse races, from the activity of`
  line `owning and maintaining such horses.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- section, “horse race” means a horse race upon which`
  line `wagering or betting may be lawfully made.]`
  line `59. Profits chargeable to tax. — ( 1 ) The provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 41 shall apply, so far`
  line `as may be, in computing the income of an assessee under section 56, as they apply in computing the`
  line `income of an assessee under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession”.`
  line `8 * * * * *`
  line `9 * * * * *`
  line `CHAPTER V`
  line `I NCOME OF OTHE R PERSONS, INCLUDED IN ASSESSEE’ S TOTAL INCOME`
  line `60. Transfer of income where there is no transfer of assets. — All income arising to any person by`
  line `virtue of a transfer whether revocable or not and whether effected before or after the commencement of`
  line `this Act shall, where there is no transfer of the assets from which the income arises, be chargeable to`
  line `income-tax as the income of the transferor and shall be included in his total income.`
  line `61. Revocable transfer of assets. — All income arising to any person by virtue of a revocable transfer`
  line `of assets shall be chargeable to income-tax as the income of the transferor and shall be included in his`
  line `total income.`
  line `62. Transfer irrevocable for a specified period. — ( 1 ) The provisions of section 61 shall not apply to`
  line `any income arising to any person by virtue of a transfer —`
  line `( i ) by way of trust which is not revocable during the lifetime of the beneficiary, and, in the case`
  line `of any other transfer, which is not revocable during the lifetime of the transferee; or`
  line `1. Clause ( iv ) omitted by Act 32 of 1971, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `2. Clause ( b ) omitted by Act 26 of 1988, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 41 of 1972, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `4. Sub s. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 30, for “sub -clauses ( iia ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 19 of 1968, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-1968).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 66 of 1976, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-6-1976).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 23 of 1986, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `8. Sub-sections ( 2 ) and ( 3 ) omitted by Act of 46 of 1986, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `9. The Explanation omitted by s. 32, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
