obj_root_law_sections_312_content:
  string
  line 312
  line `( ii ) made before the 1st day of April, 1961, which is not revocable for a period exceeding six`
  line `years:`
  line `Provided that the transferor derives no direct or indirect benefit from such income in either case.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), all income arising to any person by virtue`
  line `of any such transfer shall be chargeable to income-tax as the income of the transferor as and when the`
  line `power to revoke the transfer arises, and shall then be included in his total income.`
  line `63. “Transfer” and “revocable transfer” defined. — For the purposes of sections 60, 61 and 62 and`
  line `of this section, —`
  line `( a ) a transfer shall be deemed to be revocable if —`
  line `( i ) it contains any provision for the re-transfer directly or indirectly of the whole or any part`
  line `of the income or assets to the transferor, or`
  line `( ii ) it, in any way, gives the transferor a right to re-assume power directly or indirectly over`
  line `the whole or any part of the income or assets;`
  line `( b ) “transfer” includes any settlement, t rust, covenant, agreement or arrangement.`
  line `64. Income of individual to include income of spouse, minor child, etc. — 1 [ 2 [( 1 )] In computing`
  line `the total income of any individual, there shall be included all such income as arises directly or`
  line `indirectly —`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `( ii ) to the spouse of such individual by way of salary, commission, fees or any other form of`
  line `remuneration whether in cash or in kind from a concern in which such individual has a substantial`
  line `interest:`
  line `4 [Provided that nothing in this clause shall apply in relation to any income arising to the spouse`
  line `where the spouse possesses technical or professional qualifications and the income is solely`
  line `attributable to the application of his or her technical or professional knowledge and experience;`
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `( iv ) subject to the provisions of clause ( i ) of section 27, 6 *** to the spouse of such individual`
  line `from assets transferred directly or indirectly to the spouse by such individual otherwise than for`
  line `adequate consideration or in connection with an agreement to live apart;`
  line `7 * * * * *`
  line `( vi ) to the son ’ s wife, 8 *** of such individual, from assets transferred directly or indirectly on or`
  line `after the 1st day of June, 1973, to the son’s wife 7 *** by such individual otherwise than for adequate`
  line `consideration; 9 ***`
  line `( vii ) to any person or association of persons from assets transferred directly or indirectly`
  line `otherwise than for adequate consideration to the person or association of persons by such individual,`
  line `to the extent to which the income from such assets is for the immediate or deferred benefit of his or`
  line `her spouse; 10 *** and`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 13, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `2. Section 64 re-numbered as sub-section ( 1 ) of that section by Act 42 of 1970, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `3. Clause ( i ) omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993). Restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 as earlier omitted by`
  line `Act 4 of 1988, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `4. Restored to its original position by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 17`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `5. Clause ( iii ) omitted byAct 18 of 1992, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993). Prior to omission restored by Act 4 of 1988, s. 17`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 as earlier omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `6. The words, brackets and figures “in a case not falling under clause ( i ) of this sub- section” omitted by s. 35, ibid.`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `7. Clause ( v ) omitted by s. 35 ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `8. The words “or son’s minor child” omitted by s. 35, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `9. The words “and” omitted by Act 67 of 1984, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1985).`
  line `10. The words “or minor child or both” omit ted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
