  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_314_footnotes
  sourcePage 314
obj_root_law_sections_314_content:
  string
  line 314
  line `( b ) activity involving application of his skill, talent or specialised knowledge and experience.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, the income of the minor child shall be`
  line `included, —`
  line `( a ) where the marriage of his parents subsists, in the income of that parent whose total income`
  line `(excluding the income includible under this sub-section) is greater; or`
  line `( b ) where the marriage of his parents does not subsist, in the income of that parent who maintains`
  line `the minor child in the previous year,`
  line `and where any such income is once included in the total income of either parent, any such income`
  line `arising in any succeeding year shall not be included in the total income of the other parent, unless the`
  line `Assessing Officer is satisfied, after giving that parent an opportunity of being heard, that it is necessary so`
  line `to do.]`
  line `1 [( 2 ) Where, in the case of an individual being a member of a Hindu undivided family, any property`
  line `having been the separate property of the individual has, at any time after the 31st day of December, 1969,`
  line `been converted by the individual into property belonging to the family through the act of impressing such`
  line `separate property with the character of property belonging to the family or throwing it 2 [into the common`
  line `stock of the family or been transferred by the individual, directly or indirectly, to the family otherwise`
  line `than for adequate consideration (the property so converted or transferred being hereinafter referred to as`
  line `the converted property)], then, notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act or in`
  line `any other law for the time being in force, for the purpose of computation of the total income of the`
  line `individual under this Act for any assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 1971, —`
  line `( a ) the individual shall be deemed to have transferred the converted property, through the family,`
  line `to the members of the family for being held by them jointly;`
  line `( b ) the income derived from the converted property or any part thereof 3 *** shall be deemed to`
  line `arise to the individual and not to the family;`
  line `4 [( c ) where the converted property has been the subject-matter of a partition (whether partial or`
  line `total) amongst the members of the family, the income derived from such converted property as is`
  line `received by the spouse 5 *** on partition shall be deemed to arise to the spouse 5 *** from assets`
  line `transferred indirectly by the individual to the spouse 5 *** and the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) shall,`
  line `so far as may be, apply accordingly:]`
  line `Provided that the income referred to in clause ( b ) or clause ( c ) shall, on being included in the total`
  line `income of the individual, be excluded from the total income of the family or, as the case may be, the`
  line `spouse 5 *** of the individual.`
  line `Explanation 6 [1]. — For the purposes of sub-section ( 2 ), —`
  line `7 *** “property” includes any interest in property, movable or immovable, the proceeds of sale thereof`
  line `and any money or investment for the time being representing the proceeds of sale thereof and where the`
  line `property is converted into any other property by any method, such other property.`
  line `8 * * * * *`
  line `9 [ Explanation 2. —For the purposes of this section, “income” includes loss.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1979, s. 9 for “into the common stock of the family (such property being hereinafter referred to as the`
  line `converted property)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1980).`
  line `3. The words “in so far as it is attributable to the interest of the individual in the property of the family” omitted by Act 41 of`
  line `1975, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 13, ibid.,for clause ( c ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `5. The words “or minor child” omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1993).`
  line `6. The Explanation renumbered as Explanation 1 thereof by Act of 21 of 1979, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-1980).`
  line `7. The brackets and figure “( 1 )” omitted by Act 41 of 1975, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1976).`
  line `8. Clause ( 2 ) omitted by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 21 of 1979, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-1980).`
