  sourcePage 315
obj_root_law_sections_315_content:
  string
  line 315
  line `65. Liability of person in respect of income included in the income of another person. — Where,`
  line `by reason of the provisions contained in this Chapter or in clause ( i ) of section 27, the income from any`
  line `asset or from membership in a firm of a person other than the assessee is included in the total income of`
  line `the assessee, the person in whose name such asset stands or who is a member of the firm shall,`
  line `notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any other law for the time being in force, be liable,`
  line `on the service of a notice of demand by the 1 [Assessing Officer] in this behalf, to pay that portion of the`
  line `tax levied on the assessee which is attributable to the income so included, and the provisions of Chapter`
  line `XVII-D shall, so far as may be, apply accordingly:`
  line `Provided that where any such asset is held jointly by more than one person, they shall be jointly and`
  line `severally liable to pay the tax which is attributable to the income from the assets so included.`
  line `CHAPTER VI`
  line `AGGREGATION OF INCOME AND SET OFF OR CARRY FORWARD OF LOSS`
  line `Aggregation of income`
  line `66. Total income. — In computing the total income of an assessee, there shall be included all income`
  line `on which no income-tax is payable under Chapter VII 2 ***.`
  line `67. [ Method of computing a partner’s share in the income of the firm. ] Omitted by the Finance`
  line `Act, 1992, (18 of 1992), s. 36 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1993). Earlier amended by Act 19 of 1968, s. 30 and the Third`
  line `Schedule ( w.e.f. 1-4-1969), Act 32 of 1971, s. 13 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1971), subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 18 ( w.e.f. 1-`
  line `4-1988) or restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3 [ 67A. Method of computing a member's share in income of association of persons or body of`
  line `individuals. — ( 1 ) In computing the total income of an assessee who is a member of an association of`
  line `persons or a body of individuals wherein the shares of the members are determinate and known [other`
  line `than a company or a cooperative society or a society registered under the Societies Registration Act, 1860`
  line `(21 of 1860), or under any law corresponding to that Act in force in any part of India], whether the net`
  line `result of the computation of the total income of such association or body is a profit or a loss, his share`
  line `(whether a net profit or net loss) shall be computed as follows, namely: —`
  line `( a ) any interest, salary, bonus, commission or remuneration by whatever name called, paid to any`
  line `member in respect of the previous year shall be deducted from the total income of the association or`
  line `body and the balance ascertained and apportioned among the members in the proportions in which`
  line `they are entitled to share in the income of the association or body;`
  line `( b ) where the amount apportioned to a member under clause ( a ) is a profit, any interest, salary,`
  line `bonus, commission or remuneration aforesaid paid to the member by the association or body in`
  line `respect of the previous year shall be added to that amount, and the result shall be treated as the`
  line `member's share in the income of the association or body;`
  line `( c ) where the amount apportioned to a member under clause ( a ) is a loss, any interest, salary,`
  line `bonus, commission or remuneration aforesaid paid to the member by the association or body in`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. The words, figures and letters “and any amount in respect of which the assessee is entitled to a deduction from the amount`
  line `of income-tax on his total income with which he is chargeable for any assessment year in accordance with, and to the`
  line `extent provided in sections 87, 87A and 88” omitted by Act 20 of 1967, s. 33 and the Third Schedule (w.e.f. 1 -4-1968).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_315_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_316:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-316
