  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_316_footnotes
  sourcePage 316
obj_root_law_sections_316_content:
  string
  line 316
  line `respect of the previous year shall be adjusted against that amount, and the result shall be treated as the`
  line `member’s share in the income of the association or body.`
  line `( 2 ) The share of a member in the income or loss of the association or body, as computed under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ), shall, for the purposes of assessment, be apportioned under the various heads of income`
  line `in the same manner in which the income or loss of the association or body has been determined under`
  line `each head of income.`
  line `( 3 ) Any interest paid by a member on capital borrowed by him for the purposes of investment in the`
  line `association or body shall, in computing his share chargeable under the head “Profits and gains of business`
  line `or profession” in respect of his share in the income of the association or body, be deducted from his share.`
  line `Explanation. —In this section, “paid” has the same meaning as is assigned to it in clause ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 43.]`
  line `68. Cash credits. — Where any sum is found credited in the books of an assessee maintained for any`
  line `previous year, and the assessee offers no explanation about the nature and source thereof or the`
  line `explanation offered by him is not, in the opinion of the 1 [Assessing Officer], satisfactory, the sum so`
  line `credited may be charged to income-tax as the income of theassessee of that previous year:`
  line `2 [ Provided that where the assessee is a company (not being a company in which the public are`
  line `substantially interested), and the sum so credited consists of share application money, share capital, share`
  line `premium or any such amount by whatever name called, any explanation offered by such assessee-`
  line `company shall be deemed to be not satisfactory, unless —`
  line `( a ) the person, being a resident in whose name such credit is recorded in the books of such`
  line `company also offers an explanation about the nature and source of such sum so credited; and`
  line `( b ) such explanation in the opinion of the Assessing Officer aforesaid has been found to be`
  line `satisfactory:`
  line `Provided further that nothing contained in the first proviso shall apply if the person, in whose name`
  line `the sum referred to therein is recorded, is a venture capital fund or a venture capital company as referred`
  line `to in clause ( 23FB )of section 10.]`
  line `69. Unexplained investments. — Where in the financial year immediately preceding the assessment`
  line `year the assessee has made investments which are not recorded in the books of account, if any,`
  line `maintained by him for any source of income, and the assessee offers no explanation about the nature and`
  line `source of the investments or the explanation offered by him is not, in the opinion of the 1 [Assessing`
  line `Officer], satisfactory, the value of the investments may be deemed to be the income of the assessee of`
  line `such financial year.`
  line `3 [ 69A. Unexplained money, etc. — Where in any financial year the assessee is found to be the owner`
  line `of any money, bullion, jewellery or other valuable article and such money, bullion, jewellery or valuable`
  line `article is not recorded in the books of account, if any, maintained by him for any source of income, and`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 5 of 1964, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-1964).`
obj_root_law_sections_316_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_317:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-317
  sectionNo (317)
  orderNo 317
  title `Page 317`
  content obj_root_law_sections_317_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_317_footnotes
  sourcePage 317
obj_root_law_sections_317_content:
  string
  line 317
  line `the assessee offers no explanation about the nature and source of acquisition of the money, bullion,`
  line `jewellery or other valuable article, or the explanation offered by him is not, in the opinion of the`
  line `1 [Assessing Officer], satisfactory, the money and the value of the bullion,jewellery or other valuable`
  line `article may be deemed to be the income of the assessee for such financial year.]`
  line `2 [ 69B. Amount of investments, etc., not fully disclosed in books of account. — Where in any`
  line `financial year the assessee has made investments or is found to be the owner of any bullion, jewellery or`
  line `other valuable article, and the 1 [Assessing Officer] finds that the amount expended on making such`
  line `investments or in acquiring such bullion, jewellery or other valuable article exceeds the amount recorded`
  line `in this behalf in the books of account maintained by the assessee for any source of income, and the`
  line `assessee offers no explanation about such excess amount or the explanation offered by him is not, in the`
  line `opinion of the 1 [Assessing Officer], satisfactory, the excess amount may be deemed to be the income of`
  line `the assessee for such financial year.]`
  line `3 [69C. Unexplained expenditure, etc. — Where in any financial year an assessee has incurred any`
  line `expenditure and he offers no explanation about the source of such expenditure or part thereof, or the`
  line `explanation, if any, offered by him is not, in the opinion of the 1 [Assessing Officer], satisfactory, the`
  line `amount covered by such expenditure or part thereof, as the case may be, may be deemed to be the income`
  line `of the assessee for such financial year:`
  line `4 [ Provided that, notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, such`
  line `unexplained expenditure which is deemed to be the income of the assessee shall not be allowed as a`
  line `deduction under any head of income.]`
  line `69D. Amount borrowed or repaid on hundi. — Where any amount is borrowed on a hundi from, or`
  line `any amount due thereon is repaid to, any person otherwise than through an account payee cheque drawn`
  line `on a bank, the amount so borrowed or repaid shall be deemed to be the income of the person borrowing or`
  line `repaying the amount aforesaid for the previous year in which the amount was borrowed or repaid, as the`
  line `case may be:`
  line `Provided that, if in any case any amount borrowed on a hundi has been deemed under the provisions`
  line `of this section to be the income of any person, such person shall not be liable to be assessed again in`
  line `respect of such amount under the provisions of this section on repayment of such amount.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, the amount repaid shall include the amount of interest`
  line `paid on the amount borrowed.]`
  line `Set off, or carry forward and set off`
  line `5 [ 70. Set off of loss from one source against income from another source under the same head of`
  line `income. — ( 1 ) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, where the net result for any assessment year in`
  line `respect of any source falling under any head of income, other than “Capital gains”, is a loss, the assessee`
  line `shall be entitled to have the amount of such loss set off against his income from any other source under`
  line `the same head.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 27, for section 70 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_317_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_318:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-318
  sectionNo (318)
  orderNo 318
  title `Page 318`
  content obj_root_law_sections_318_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_318_footnotes
  sourcePage 318
obj_root_law_sections_318_content:
  string
  line 318
  line `( 2 ) Where the result of the computation made for any assessment year under sections 48 to 55in`
  line `respect of any short-term capital asset is a loss, the assessee shall be entitled to have the amount of such`
  line `loss set off against the income, if any, as arrived at under a similar computation made for the assessment`
  line `year in respect of any other capital asset.`
  line `( 3 ) Where the result of the computation made for any assessment year under sections 48 to 55 in`
  line `respect of any capital asset (other than a short-term capital asset) is a loss, the assessee shall be entitled to`
  line `have the amount of such loss set off against the income, if any, as arrived at under a similar computation`
  line `made for the assessment year in respect of any other capital asset not being a short-term capital asset.]`
  line `1 [ 71.Set off of loss from one head against income from another. — ( 1 ) Where in respect of any`
  line `assessment year the net result of the computation under any head of income, other than “Capital gains”, is`
  line `a loss and the assessee has no income under the head “Capital gains”, he shall, subject to the provisions of`
  line `this Chapter, be entitled to have the amount of such loss set off against his income, if any, assessable for`
  line `that assessment year under any other head.`
  line `( 2 ) Where in respect of any assessment year, the net result of the computation under any head of`
  line `income, other than “Capital gains”, is a loss and the assessee has income assessable under the head`
  line `“Capital gains”, such loss may, su bject to the provisions of this Chapter, be set off against his income, if`
  line `any, assessable for that assessment year under any head of income including the head “Capital gains”`
  line `(whether relating to short-term capital assets or any other capital assets).`
  line `2 [( 2A ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ), where in respect of`
  line `any assessment year, the net result of the computation under the head “Profits and gains of business or`
  line `profession” is a loss and the assessee has income assessable under the head “Salaries”, the assessee shall`
  line `not be entitled to have such loss set off against such income.]`
  line `( 3 ) Where in respect of any assessment year, the net result of the computation under the head “Capital`
  line `gains” is a loss and the assessee ha s income assessable under any other head of income, the assessee shall`
  line `not be entitled to have such loss set off against income under the other head.]`
  line `3 [( 3A ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ), where in respect of`
  line `any assessment year, the net result of the computation under the head “Income from house property” is a`
  line `loss and the assessee has income assessable under any other head of income, the assessee shall not be`
  line `entitled to set off such loss, to the extent the amount of the loss exceeds two lakh rupees, against income`
  line `under the other head.]`
  line `4 [( 4 ) Where the net result of the computation under the head “Income from house property” is a loss,`
  line `in respect of the assessment years commencing on the 1st day of April, 1995 and the 1st day of April,`
  line `1996, such loss shall be first set off under sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) and thereafter the loss referred to`
  line `in section 71A shall be set off in the relevant assessment year in accordance with the provisions of that`
  line section.]
  line `5 [ 71A.Tran sitional provisions for set off of loss under the head “Income from house`
  line `property”. — Where in respect of the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1993`
  line `or the 1st day of April, 1994, the net result of the computation under the head “Income from`
  line `house property” is a loss, such loss in so far as it relates to interest on borrowed capital referred to`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 23, for section 71 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
  line `3. Ins.by Act 7 of 2017, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 21, for sub-section ( 4 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 22, ibid., for section 71A (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
