  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_319_footnotes
  sourcePage 319
obj_root_law_sections_319_content:
  string
  line 319
  line `in clause ( vi ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 24 and to the extent it has not been set off shall be carried`
  line `forward and set off in the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1995, and the balance, if`
  line `any, in the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1996, against the income under any`
  line head.]
  line `1 [ 71B.Carry forward and set off of loss from house property. — Where for any assessment year the`
  line `net result of computation under the head “Income from house property” is a loss to the assessee and such`
  line `loss cannot be or is not wholly set off against income from any other head of income in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of section 71, so much of the loss as has not been so set-off or where he has no income`
  line `under any other head, the whole loss shall, subject to the other provisions of this Chapter, be carried`
  line `forward to the following assessment year and —`
  line `( i ) be set off against the income from house property assessable for that assessment year; and`
  line `( ii ) the loss, if any, which has not been set off wholly, the amount of loss not so set off,`
  line `shall be carried forward to the following assessment year, not being more than eight assessment years`
  line `immediately succeeding the assessment year for which the loss was first computed.]`
  line `72.Carry forward and set off of business losses. — 2 [( 1 ) Where for any assessment year, the net`
  line `result of the computation under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession” is a loss to the`
  line `assessee, not being a loss sustained in a speculation business, and such loss cannot be or is not wholly set`
  line `off against income under any head of income in accordance with the provisions of section 71, so much of`
  line `the loss as has not been so set off or, 3 *** where he has no income under any other head, the whole loss`
  line `shall, subject to the other provisions of this Chapter, be carried forward to the following assessment year,`
  line `and —`
  line `( i ) it shall be set off against the profits and gains, if any, of any business or profession carried on`
  line `by him and assessable for that assessment year;`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `( ii ) if the loss cannot be wholly so set off, the amount of loss not so set off shall be carried`
  line `forward to the following assessment year and so on:]`
  line `5 [Provided that where the whole or any part of such loss is sustained in any such business as is`
  line `referred to in section 33B which is discontinued in the circumstances specified in that section, and,`
  line `thereafter, at any time before the expiry of the period of three years referred to in that section, such`
  line `business is re-established, reconstructed or revived by the assessee, so much of the loss as is attributable`
  line `to such business shall be carried forward to the assessment year relevant to the previous year in which the`
  line `business is so re-established, reconstructed or revived, and —`
  line `( a ) it shall be set off against the profits and gains, if any, of that business or any other business`
  line `carried on by him and assessable for that assessment year; and`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 1962, s. 6, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `3. The words, brackets and figure ‘where the assesse has income only under the head “capital gains” relating to capital assets`
  line `other than short-term capital assets and has exercised the option under sub-section ( 2 ) of that section or’ omitted by Act`
  line `11 of 1987, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `4. The proviso omitted by Act 27 of 1999, s. 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `5. Added by Act 20 of 1967, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-4-1967).`
