  content obj_root_law_sections_320_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_320_footnotes
  sourcePage 320
obj_root_law_sections_320_content:
  string
  line 320
  line `( b ) if the loss cannot be wholly so set off, the amount of loss not so set off shall, in case the`
  line `business so re-established, reconstructed or revived continues to be carried on by the assessee, be`
  line `carried forward to the following assessment year and so on for seven assessment years immediately`
  line succeeding.]
  line `( 2 ) Where any allowance or part thereof is, under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 32 or sub-section ( 4 )`
  line `of section 35, to be carried forward, effect shall first be given to the provisions of this section.`
  line `( 3 ) No loss 1 [(other than the loss referred to in the proviso to sub-section ( 1 ) of this section)] shall be`
  line `carried forward under this section for more than eight assessment years immediately succeeding the`
  line `assessment year for which the loss was first computed.`
  line `2 [72A. Provisions relating to carry forward and set off of accumulated loss and unabsorbed`
  line `depreciation allowance in amalgamation or demerger, etc. — 3 [( 1 ) Where there has been an`
  line `amalgamation of —`
  line `( a ) a company owning an industrial undertaking or a ship or a hotel with another company; or`
  line `( b ) a banking company referred to in clause ( c ) of section 5 of the Banking Regulation`
  line `Act, 1949 (10 of 1949) with a specified bank; or`
  line `( c ) one or more public sector company or companies engaged in the business of operation of`
  line `aircraft with one or more public sector company or companies engaged in similar business,`
  line `then, notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, the accumulated loss and`
  line `the unabsorbed depreciation of the amalgamating company shall be deemed to be the loss or, as the`
  line `case may be, allowance for unabsorbed depreciation of the amalgamated company for the previous`
  line `year in which the amalgamation was effected, and other provisions of this Act relating to set off and`
  line `carry forward of loss and allowance for depreciation shall apply accordingly.]`
  line `4 [( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), the accumulated loss shall not be set off`
  line `or carried forward and the unabsorbed depreciation shall not be allowed in the assessment of the`
  line `amalgamated company unless —`
  line `( a ) the amalgamating company —`
  line `( i ) has been engaged in the business, in which the accumulated loss occurred or depreciation`
  line `remains unabsorbed, for three or more years;`
  line `( ii ) has held continuously as on the date of the amalgamation at least three-fourths of the`
  line `book value of fixed assets held by it two years prior to the date of amalgamation;`
  line `( b ) the amalgamated company —`
  line `( i ) holds continuously for a minimum period of five years from the date of amalgamation at`
  line `least three-fourths of the book value of fixed assets of the amalgamating company acquired in a`
  line `scheme of amalgamation;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-4-1967).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 38, for section 72A (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 20, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 33, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_320_footnotes:
