obj_root_law_sections_321:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-321
  sectionNo (321)
  orderNo 321
  title `Page 321`
  content obj_root_law_sections_321_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_321_footnotes
  sourcePage 321
obj_root_law_sections_321_content:
  string
  line 321
  line `( ii ) continues the business of the amalgamating company for a minimum period of five years`
  line `from the date of amalgamation;`
  line `( iii ) fulfils such other conditions as may be prescribedto ensure the revival of the business of`
  line `the amalgamating company or to ensure that the amalgamation is for genuine business purpose.]`
  line `( 3 ) In a case where any of the conditions laid down in sub-section ( 2 ) are not complied with, the set`
  line `off of loss or allowance of depreciation made in any previous year in the hands of the amalgamated`
  line `company shall be deemed to be the income of the amalgamated company chargeable to tax for the year in`
  line `which such conditions are not complied with.`
  line `( 4 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provisions of this Act, in the case of a demerger,`
  line `the accumulated loss and the allowance for unabsorbed depreciation of the demerged company shall —`
  line `( a ) where such loss or unabsorbed depreciation is directly relatable to the undertakings`
  line `transferred to the resulting company, be allowed to be carried forward and set off in the hands of the`
  line `resulting company;`
  line `( b ) where such loss or unabsorbed depreciation is not directly relatable to the undertakings`
  line `transferred to the resulting company, be apportioned between the demerged company and the`
  line `resulting company in the same proportion in which the assets of the undertakings have been retained`
  line `by the demerged company and transferred to the resulting company, and be allowed to be carried`
  line `forward and set off in the hands of the demerged company or the resulting company, as the case may`
  line be.
  line `( 5 ) The Central Government may, for the purposes of this Act, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `specify such conditions as it considers necessary to ensure that the demerger is for genuine business`
  line purposes.
  line `( 6 ) Where there has been reorganisation of business, whereby, a firm is succeeded by a company`
  line `fulfilling the conditions laid down in clause ( xiii ) of section 47 or a proprietary concern is succeeded by a`
  line `company fulfilling the conditions laid down in clause ( xiv ) of section 47, then, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other provision of this Act, the accumulated loss and the unabsorbed depreciation of the`
  line `predecessor firm or the proprietary concern, as the case may be, shall be deemed to be the loss or`
  line `allowance for depreciation of the successor company for the purpose of previous year in which business`
  line `reorganisation was effected and other provisions of this Act relating to set off and carry forward of loss`
  line `and allowance for depreciation shall apply accordingly:`
  line `Provided that if any of the conditions laid down in the proviso to clause ( xiii ) or the proviso to`
  line `clause ( xiv )to section 47 are not complied with, the set off of loss or allowance of depreciation made in`
  line `any previous year in the hands of the successor company, shall be deemed to be the income of the`
  line `company chargeable to tax in the year in which such conditions are not complied with.`
  line `1 [( 6A ) Where there has been reorganisation of business whereby a private company or unlisted public`
  line `company is succeeded by a limited liability partnership fulfilling the conditions laid down in the proviso`
  line `to clause ( xiiib ) of section 47, then, notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act,`
  line `the accumulated loss and the unabsorbed depreciation of the predecessor company, shall be deemed to be`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-4-2011).`
obj_root_law_sections_321_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_322:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-322
  sectionNo (322)
