  title `Page 322`
  content obj_root_law_sections_322_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_322_footnotes
  sourcePage 322
obj_root_law_sections_322_content:
  string
  line 322
  line `the loss or allowance for depreciation of the successor limited liability partnership for the purpose of the`
  line `previous year in which business reorganisation was effected and other provisions of this Act relating to`
  line `set off and carry forward of loss and allowance for depreciation shall apply accordingly:`
  line `Provided that if any of the conditions laid down in the proviso to clause ( xiiib ) of section 47 are not`
  line `complied with, the set off of loss or allowance of depreciation made in any previous year in the hands of`
  line `the successor limited liability partnership, shall be deemed to be the income of the limited liability`
  line `partnership chargeable to tax in the year in which such conditions are not complied with.]`
  line `( 7 ) For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `1 [( a ) “accumulated loss” means so much of the loss of the predecessor firm or the proprietary`
  line `concern or the private company or unlisted public company before conversion into limited liability`
  line `partnership or the amalgamating company or the demerged company, as the case may be, under the`
  line `head “Profits and gains of business or profession” (not being a loss sustained in a speculation`
  line `business) which such predecessor firm or the proprietary concern or the company or amalgamating`
  line `company or demerged company, would have been entitled to carry forward and set off under the`
  line `provisions of section 72if the reorganisation of business or conversion or amalgamation or demerger`
  line `had not taken place;]`
  line `2 [( aa ) “industrial undertaking” means any undertaking which is engaged in—`
  line `( i ) the manufacture or processing of goods; or`
  line `( ii ) the manufacture of computer software; or`
  line `( iii ) the business of generation or distribution of electricity or any other form of power; or`
  line `3 [( iiia ) the business of providing telecommunication services, whether basic or cellular,`
  line `including radio paging, domestic satellite service, network of trunking, broadband network and`
  line `internet services; or]`
  line `( iv ) mining; or`
  line `( v ) the construction of ships, aircrafts or rail systems;]`
  line `( b ) “unabsorbed depreciation” means so much of the allowance for depreciation of the`
  line `predecessor firm or the proprietary concern or the private company or unlisted public company before`
  line `conversion into limited liability partnership or the amalgamating company or the demerged company,`
  line `as the case may be, which remains to be allowed and which would have been allowed to the`
  line `predecessor firm or the proprietary concern or the company or amalgamating company or demerged`
  line `company, as the case may be, under the provisions of this Act, if the reorganisation of business or`
  line `conversion or amalgamation or demerger had not taken place;]`
  line `4 [( c ) “specified bank” means the State Bank of India constituted under the State Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1955 (23 of 1955) or a subsidiary bank as defined in the State Bank of India (Subsidiary Banks)`
  line `Act, 1959 (38 of 1959) or a corresponding new bank constituted under section 3 of the Banking`
  line `Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970) or under section 3 of`
  line `the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1980 (40 of 1980).]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 22, for clauses ( a ) and ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2011).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_322_footnotes:
