  title `Page 323`
  content obj_root_law_sections_323_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_323_footnotes
  sourcePage 323
obj_root_law_sections_323_content:
  string
  line 323
  line `1 [ 72AA. Provisions relating to carry forward and set-off of accumulated loss and unabsorbed`
  line `depreciation allowance in scheme of amalgamation of banking company in certain cases. —`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-clauses ( i ) to ( iii ) of clause ( 1B ) of section 2 or section 72A`
  line `where there has been an amalgamation of a banking company with any other banking institution under a`
  line `scheme sanctioned and brought into force by the Central Government under sub-section ( 7 ) of section 45`
  line `of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), the accumulated loss and the unabsorbed depreciation`
  line `of such banking company shall be deemed to be the loss or, as the case may be, allowance for`
  line `depreciation of such banking institution for the previous year in which the scheme of amalgamation was`
  line `brought into force and other provisions of this Act relating to set-off and carry forward of loss and`
  line `allowance for depreciation shall apply accordingly.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “accumulated loss” means so much of the loss of the amalgamating banking company under`
  line `the head “Profits and gains of business or profession” (not being a loss sustained in a speculation`
  line `business) which such amalgamating banking company, would have been entitled to carry forward and`
  line `set-off under the provisions of section 72 if the amalgamation had not taken place;`
  line `( ii ) “banking company” shall have the same meaning assigned to it in clause ( c ) of section 5 of`
  line `the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949);`
  line `( iii ) “banking institution” shall have the same meaning assigned to it in sub -section ( 15 ) of`
  line `section 45 of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949);`
  line `( iv ) “unabsorbed depreciation” means so much of the allowance for depreciation of the`
  line `amalgamating banking company which remains to be allowed and which would have been allowed to`
  line `such banking company if amalgamation had not taken place.]`
  line `2 [ 72AB. Provisions relating to carry forward and set off of accumulated loss and unabsorbed`
  line `depreciation allowance in business reorganisation of co-operative banks. — ( 1 ) The assessee, being a`
  line `successor co-operative bank, shall, in a case where the amalgamation has taken place during the previous`
  line `year, be allowed to set off the accumulated loss and the unabsorbed depreciation, if any, of the`
  line `predecessor co-operative bank as if the amalgamation had not taken place, and all the other provisions of`
  line `this Act relating to set off and carry forward of loss and allowance for depreciation shall apply`
  line accordingly.
  line `( 2 ) The provisions of this section shall apply if —`
  line `( a ) the predecessor co-operative bank —`
  line `( i ) has been engaged in the business of banking for three or more years; and`
  line `( ii ) has held at least three-fourths of the book value of fixed assets as on the date of the`
  line `business reorganisation, continuously for two years prior to the date of business reorganisation;`
  line `( b ) the successor co-operative bank —`
  line `( i ) holds at least three-fourths of the book value of fixed assets of the predecessor`
  line `co-operative bank acquired through business reorganisation, continuously for a minimum period`
  line `of five years immediately succeeding the date of business reorganisation;`
  line `( ii ) continues the business of the predecessor co-operative bank for a minimum period of five`
  line `years from the date of business reorganisation; and`
  line `( iii ) fulfils such other conditions as may be prescribed to ensure the revival of the business of`
  line `the predecessor co-operative bank or to ensure that the business reorganisation is for genuine`
  line `business purpose.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_323_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_324:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-324
  sectionNo (324)
  orderNo 324
  title `Page 324`
  content obj_root_law_sections_324_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_324_footnotes
  sourcePage 324
obj_root_law_sections_324_content:
  string
  line 324
  line `( 3 ) The amount of set-off of the accumulated loss and unabsorbed depreciation, if any, allowable to`
  line `the assessee being a resulting co-operative bank shall be, —`
  line `( i ) the accumulated loss or unabsorbed depreciation of the demerged co-operative bank if the`
  line `whole of the amount of such loss or unabsorbed depreciation is directly relatable to the undertakings`
  line `transferred to the resulting co-operative bank; or`
  line `( ii ) the amount which bears the same proportion to the accumulated loss or unabsorbed`
  line `depreciation of the demerged co-operative bank as the assets of the undertaking transferred to the`
  line `resulting co-operative bank bears to the assets of the demerged co-operative bank if such accumulated`
  line `loss or unabsorbed depreciation is not directly relatable to the undertakings transferred to the resulting`
  line `co-operative bank.`
  line `( 4 ) The Central Government may, for the purposes of this section, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify such other conditions as it considers necessary, other than those prescribed under sub-`
  line `clause (iii) of clause (b) of sub-section ( 2 ), to ensure that the business reorganisation is for genuine`
  line `business purposes.`
  line `( 5 ) The period commencing from the beginning of the previous year and ending on the date`
  line `immediately preceding the date of business reorganisation, and the period commencing from the date of`
  line `such business reorganisation and ending with the previous year shall be deemed to be two different`
  line `previous years for the purposes of set off and carry forward of loss and allowance for depreciation.`
  line `( 6 ) In a case where the conditions specified in sub-section ( 2 ) or notified under sub-section ( 4 ) are not`
  line `complied with, the set off of accumulated loss or unabsorbed depreciation allowed in any previous year to`
  line `the successor co-operative bank shall be deemed to be the income of the successor co-operative bank`
  line `chargeable to tax for the year in which the conditions are not complied with.`
  line `( 7 ) For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “accumulated loss” means so much of loss of the amalgamating co -operative bank or the`
  line `demerged co- operative bank, as the case may be, under the head “Profits and gains of business or`
  line `profession” (not being a loss sustained in a speculation business) which such amalgamating co -`
  line `operative bank or the demerged co-operative bank, would have been entitled to carry forward and set-`
  line `off under the provisions of section 72 as if the business reorganisation had not taken place;`
  line `( b ) “unabsorbed depreciation” means so much of the allowance for depreciation of the`
  line `amalgamating co-operative bank or the demerged co-operative bank, as the case may be, which`
  line `remains to be allowed and which would have been allowed to such bank as if the business`
  line `reorganisation had not taken place;`
  line `( c ) the expressions “amalgamated co - operative bank”, “amalgamating co - operative bank”,`
  line `“amalgamation”, “business reorganisation”, “co - operative bank”, “demerged co - operative bank”,`
  line `“demerger”, “predecessor co - operative bank”, “successor co - operative bank” and “resulting`
  line `co- operative bank” shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in section 44DB.]`
  line `73. Losses in speculation business. — ( 1 ) Any loss, computed in respect of a speculation business`
  line `carried on by the assessee, shall not be set off except against profits and gains, if any, of another`
  line `speculation business.`
  line `( 2 ) Where for any assessment year any loss computed in respect of a speculation business has not`
  line `been wholly set off under sub-section ( 1 ), so much of the loss as is not so set off or the whole loss where`
  line `the assessee had no income from any other speculation business, shall, subject to the other provisions of`
  line `this Chapter, be carried forward to the following assessment year, and —`
  line `( i ) it shall be set off against the profits and gains, if any, of any speculation business carried on`
  line `by him assessable for that assessment year; and`
obj_root_law_sections_324_footnotes:
  string
  line
