  sourcePage 325
obj_root_law_sections_325_content:
  string
  line 325
  line `( ii ) if the loss cannot be wholly so set off, the amount of loss not so set off shall be carried`
  line `forward to the following assessment year and soon.`
  line `( 3 ) In respect of allowance on account of depreciation or capital expenditure on scientific research,`
  line `the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 72 shall apply in relation to speculation business as they apply`
  line `in relation to any other business.`
  line `( 4 ) No loss shall be carried forward under this section for more than 1 [four assessment years]`
  line `immediately succeeding the assessment year for which the loss was first computed.`
  line `2 [ Explanation. — Where any part of the business of a company ( 3 [other than a company whose gross`
  line `total income consists mainly of income which is chargeable under the heads “Interest on securities”,`
  line `“Income from house property”, “Capital gains” and “Income from other sources”], or a company 4 [the`
  line `principal business of which is the business of trading in shares or banking] or the granting of loans and`
  line `advances) consists in the purchase and sale of shares of other companies, such company shall, for the`
  line `purposes of this section, be deemed to be carrying on a speculation business to the extent to which the`
  line `business consists of the purchase and sale of such shares.]`
  line `5 [73A. Carry forward and set off of losses by specified business. — ( 1 ) Any loss, computed in`
  line `respect of any specified business referred to in section 35AD shall not be set off except against profits and`
  line `gains, if any, of any other specified business.`
  line `( 2 ) Where for any assessment year any loss computed in respect of the specified business referred to`
  line `in sub-section ( 1 ) has not been wholly set off under sub-section ( 1 ), so much of the loss as is not so set off`
  line `or the whole loss where the assessee has no income from any other specified business, shall, subject to the`
  line `other provisions of this Chapter, be carried forward to the following assessment year, and —`
  line `( i ) it shall be set off against the profits and gains, if any, of any specified business carried on by`
  line `him assessable for that assessment year; and`
  line `( ii ) if the loss cannot be wholly so set off, the amount of loss not so set off shall be carried`
  line `forward to the following assessment year and so on.]`
  line `6 [ 74. Losses under the head “Capital gains”. — 7 [( 1 ) Where in respect of any assessment year, the`
  line `net result of the computation under the head “Capital gains” is a loss to the assessee, the whole loss shall,`
  line `subject to the other provisions of this Chapter, be carried forward to the following assessment year, and —`
  line `( a ) in so far as such loss relates to a short-term capital asset, it shall be set off against income, if`
  line `any, under the head “Capital gains” assessable for that assessment year in respect of any other capital`
  line asset;
  line `( b ) in so far as such loss relates to a long-term capital asset, it shall be set off against income, if`
  line `any, under the head “Capital gains” assessable for that assessment year in respect of any other capital`
  line `asset not being a short-term capital asset;`
  line `( c ) if the loss cannot be wholly so set off, the amount of loss not so set off shall be carried`
  line `forward to the following assessment year and so on.]`
  line `( 2 ) No loss shall be carried forward under this section for more than eight assessment years`
  line `immediately succeeding the assessment year for which the loss was first computed.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 20, for “eight assessment years” (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-1977).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 74, for “other than an investment company, as defined in clause ( ii ) of section 109”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 26, f or “the principal business of which is the business of banking” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2015).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 31, for section 74 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 29, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
