obj_root_law_sections_326_content:
  string
  line 326
  line `1 * * * * *]`
  line `2 [ 74A. Losses from certain specified sources falling under the head “Income from other`
  line `sources”. — 3 * * * * *`
  line `4 [( 3 ) 5 *** In the case of an assessee, being the owner of horses maintained by him for running in`
  line `horse races (such horses being hereafter in this sub-section referred to as race horses), 6 [the amount of`
  line `loss incurred by the assessee in the activity of owning and maintaining race horses in any assessment year`
  line `shall not be set off against income, if any, from any source other than the activity of owning and`
  line `maintaining race horses in that year and] shall, subject to the other provisions of this Chapter, be carried`
  line `forward to the following assessment year and —`
  line `( a ) it shall be set off against the income, if any, 7 [from the activity of owning and maintaining`
  line `race horses,] assessable for that assessment year:`
  line `Provided that the activity of owning and maintaining race horses is carried on by him in the`
  line `previous year relevant for that assessment year; and`
  line `( b ) if the loss cannot be wholly so set off, the amount of loss not so set off shall be carried`
  line `forward to the following assessment year and so on; so, however, that no portion of the loss shall be`
  line `carried forward for more than four assessment years immediately succeeding the assessment year for`
  line `which the loss was first computed.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section —`
  line `( a ) “amount of loss incurred by the assesse e in the activity of owning and maintaining race`
  line `horses” means—`
  line `( i ) in a case where the assessee has no income by way of stake money, the amount of`
  line `expenditure (not being in the nature of capital expenditure) laid out or expended by him wholly`
  line `and exclusively for the purposes of maintaining race horses;`
  line `( ii ) in a case where the assessee has income by way of stake money, the amount by which`
  line `such income falls short of the amount of expenditure (not being in the nature of capital`
  line `expenditure) laid out or expended by the assessee wholly and exclusively for the purposes of`
  line `maintaining race horses;`
  line `( b ) “horse race” means a horse race upon which wagering or betting may be lawfully made;`
  line `( c ) “income by way of stake money” means the gross amount of prize mone y received on a race`
  line `horse or race horses by the owner thereof on account of the horse or horses or any one or more of the`
  line `horses winning or being placed second or in any lower position in horse races.]`
  line `8 [75. Losses of firms. — Where the assessee is a firm, any loss in relation to the assessment year`
  line `commencing on or before the 1st day of April, 1992, which could not be set off against any other income`
  line `of the firm and which had been apportioned to a partner of the firm but could not be set off by such`
  line `partner prior to the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1993, then, such loss shall be`
  line `allowed to be set off against the income of the firm subject to the condition that the partner continues in`
  line `the said firm and to be carried forward for set off under sections 70, 71, 72, 73, 74 and 74A.]`
  line `1. Sub-section ( 3 ) omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `3. Sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) omitted by Act 23 of 1986, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 1974, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-1975).`
  line `5. The words “Where for any assessment year” omitted by Act 23 of 1986, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1987).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for “from the source specified in clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 2 )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1987).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 39, for sections 75, 76 and 77 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993). Earlier amended by Act 20 of 1974, s. 13`
  line `(w.e.f 1-4-1975), Act 11 of 1987, s. 74 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988), omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989) and restored`
  line `by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
