  sourcePage 327
obj_root_law_sections_327_content:
  string
  line 327
  line `78. Carry forward and set off of losses in case of change in constitution of firm or on`
  line `succession. — 1 [( 1 ) Where a change has occurred in the constitution of a firm, nothing in this Chapter shall`
  line `entitle the firm to have carried forward and set off so much of the loss proportionate to the share of a`
  line `retired or deceased partner as exceeds his share of profits, if any, in the firm in respect of the previous`
  line year.]
  line `( 2 ) Where any person carrying on any business or profession has been succeeded in such capacity by`
  line `another person otherwise than by inheritance, nothing in this Chapter shall entitle any person other than`
  line `the person incurring the loss to have it carried forward and set off against his income.`
  line `2 [ 79. Carry forward and set off of losses in case of certain companies. — Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Chapter, where a change in shareholding has taken place in a previous year, —`
  line `( a ) in the case of a company not being a company in which the public are substantially interested`
  line `and other than a company referred to in clause ( b ), no loss incurred in any year prior to the previous`
  line `year shall be carried forward and set off against the income of the previous year, unless on the last`
  line `day of the previous year, the shares of the company carrying not less than fifty-one per cent. of the`
  line `voting power were beneficially held by persons who beneficially held shares of the company carrying`
  line `not less than fifty-one per cent. of the voting power on the last day of the year or years in which the`
  line `loss was incurred;`
  line `( b ) in the case of a company, not being a company in which the public are substantially interested`
  line `but being an eligible start-up as referred to in section 80-IAC, the loss incurred in any year prior to`
  line `the previous year shall be carried forward and set off against the income of the previous year, if, all`
  line `the shareholders of such company who held shares carrying voting power on the last day of the year`
  line `or years in which the loss was incurred, —`
  line `( i ) continue to hold those shares on the last day of such previous year; and`
  line `( ii ) such loss has been incurred during the period of seven years beginning from the year in`
  line `which such company is incorporated:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall apply to a case where a change in the`
  line `said voting power and shareholding takes place in a previous year consequent upon the death of a`
  line `shareholder or on account of transfer of shares by way of gift to any relative of the shareholder`
  line `making such gift:`
  line `Provided further that nothing contained in this section shall apply to any change in the`
  line `shareholding of an Indian company which is a subsidiary of a foreign company as a result of`
  line `amalgamation or demerger of a foreign company subject to the condition that fifty-one per cent.`
  line `shareholders of the amalgamating or demerged foreign company continue to be the shareholders`
  line `of the amalgamated or the resulting foreign company.]`
  line `3 [Provided also that nothing contained in this section shall apply to a company where a`
  line `change in the shareholding takes place in a previous year pursuant to a resolution plan approved`
  line `under the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016, after affording a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard to the jurisdictional Principal Commissioner or Commissioner.]`
  line `80. Submission of return for losses. — Notwithstanding anything contained in this Chapter, no loss`
  line `which has not been determined in pursuance of a return filed 4 [in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ) of section 139], shall be carried forward and set off under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 72 or`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 73 5 [or sub-section ( 2 ) of section 73A] or 6 [sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 3 ) of`
  line `section 74] 7 [or sub-section ( 3 ) of section 74A].`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 40, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1993). Earlier subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 20`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1989) and restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 32, for section 39 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 126, for “within the time allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139 or within such further`
  line `time as may be allowed by the Income- tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 74, for “sub -section ( 1 ) of section 74” (w. e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 20 of 1974, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-1975).`
