obj_root_law_sections_330_content:
  string
  line 330
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 [ 80C. Deduction in respect of life insurance premia, deferred annuity, contributions to`
  line `provident fund, subscription to certain equity shares or debentures, etc. — ( 1 ) In computing the total`
  line `income of an assessee, being an individual or a Hindu undivided family, there shall be deducted, in`
  line `accordance with and subject to the provisions of this section, the whole of the amount paid or deposited in`
  line `the previous year, being the aggregate of the sums referred to in sub-section ( 2 ), as does not exceed 5 [one`
  line `hundred and fifty thousand rupees].`
  line `( 2 ) The sums referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be any sums paid or deposited in the previous year by`
  line `the assessee —`
  line `( i ) to effect or to keep in force an insurance on the life of persons specified in sub-section ( 4 );`
  line `( ii ) to effect or to keep in force a contract for a deferred annuity, not being an annuity plan`
  line `referred to in clause ( xii ), on the life of persons specified in sub-section ( 4 ):`
  line `Provided that such contract does not contain a provision for the exercise by the insured of an`
  line `option to receive a cash payment in lieu of the payment of the annuity;`
  line `( iii ) by way of deduction from the salary payable by or on behalf of the Government to any`
  line `individual being a sum deducted in accordance with the conditions of his service, for the purpose of`
  line `securing to him a deferred annuity or making provision for his spouse or children, in so far as the sum`
  line `so deducted does not exceed one-fifth of the salary;`
  line `( iv ) as a contribution by an individual to any provident fund to which the Provident`
  line `Funds Act, 1925 (19 of 1925) applies;`
  line `( v ) as a contribution to any provident fund set up by the Central Government and notified by it in`
  line `this behalf in the Official Gazette, where such contribution is to an account standing in the name of`
  line `any person specified in sub-section ( 4 );`
  line `( vi ) as a contribution by an employee to a recognised provident fund;`
  line `( vii ) as a contribution by an employee to an approved superannuation fund;`
  line `( viii ) 6 [as subscription, in the name of any person specified in sub-section ( 4 ), to] any such`
  line `security of the Central Government or any such deposit scheme as that Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf;`
  line `( ix ) as subscription to any such savings certificate as defined in clause ( c ) of section 2 of the`
  line `Government Savings Certificates Act, 1959 (46 of 1959), as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf;`
  line `( x ) as a contribution, in the name of any person specified in sub-section ( 4 ), for participation in`
  line `the Unit-linked Insurance Plan, 1971 (hereafter in this section referred to as the Unit-linked Insurance`
  line `Plan) specified in Schedule II of the Unit Trust of India (Transfer of Undertaking and Repeal)`
  line `Act, 2002 (58 of 2002);`
  line `( xi ) as a contribution in the name of any person specified in sub-section ( 4 ) for participation in`
  line `any such unit-linked insurance plan of the LIC Mutual Fund 7 [referred to in clause ( 23D )] of section`
  line `10, as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf;`
  line `( xii ) to effect or to keep in force a contract for such annuity plan of the Life Insurance`
  line `Corporation or any other insurer as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify;`
  line `1. Clause ( 7 ) omitted by Act 16 of 1972, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line `2. Clause ( 8 ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Clause ( 9 ) omitted by Act 41 of 1975, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006). Earlier omitted by Act 12 of 1990, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 27, for “one lakh rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2015).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 16, for “as subscription to” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2015).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 16, for “ notified under clause ( 23D )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2007).`
