obj_root_law_sections_332_content:
  string
  line 332
  line `( 6 ) any company in which the public are substantially interested or any co-operative`
  line `society, where such company or co-operative society is engaged in the business of financing`
  line `the construction of houses, or`
  line `( 7 ) the assessee’s employer where such employer is an authority or a board or a`
  line `corporation or any other body established or constituted under a Central or State Act, or`
  line `( 8 ) the assessee’s employ er where such employer is a public company or a public sector`
  line `company or a university established by law or a college affiliated to such university or a local`
  line `authority or a co-operative society; or`
  line `( d ) stamp duty, registration fee and other expenses for the purpose of transfer of such house`
  line `property to the assessee,`
  line `but shall not include any payment towards or by way of —`
  line `( A ) the admission fee, cost of share and initial deposit which a shareholder of a company or a member`
  line `of a co-operative society has to pay for becoming such shareholder or member; or`
  line `( B ) the cost of any addition or alteration to, or renovation or repair of, the house property which is`
  line `carried out after the issue of the completion certificate in respect of the house property by the authority`
  line `competent to issue such certificate or after the house property or any part thereof has either been occupied`
  line `by the assessee or any other person on his behalf or been let out; or`
  line `( C ) any expenditure in respect of which deduction is allowable under the provisions of section 24;`
  line `( xix ) as subscription to equity shares or debentures forming part of any eligible issue of capital`
  line `approved by the Board on an application made by a public company or as subscription to any eligible`
  line `issue of capital by any public financial institution in the prescribed form.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( i ) “eligible issue of capital” means an issue made by a public company formed and registered`
  line `in India or a public financial institution and the entire proceeds of the issue are utilised wholly`
  line `and exclusively for the purposes of any business referred to in sub-section ( 4 ) of section 80-IA;`
  line `( ii ) “public company” shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 3 of the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line `( iii ) “public financial institution” shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 4A of the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line `( xx ) as subscription to any units of any mutual fund referred to in clause ( 23D ) of section 10 and`
  line `approved by the Board on an application made by such mutual fund in the prescribed form:`
  line `Provided that this clause shall apply if the amount of subscription to such units is subscribed only`
  line `in the eligible issue of capital of any company.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause “eligible issue of capital” means an issue referred`
  line `to in clause ( i ) of the Explanation to clause ( xix ) of sub-section ( 2 );`
  line `1 [( xxi ) as term deposit —`
  line `( a ) for a fixed period of not less than five years with a scheduled bank; and`
  line `( b ) which is in accordance with a scheme framed and notified, by the Central Government, in`
  line `the Official Gazette for the purposes of this clause.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
