obj_root_law_sections_333_content:
  string
  line 333
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, “scheduled bank” means the State Bank of India`
  line `constituted under the State Bank of India Act, 1955 (23 of 1955), or a subsidiary bank as defined in`
  line `the State Bank of India (Subsidiary Banks) Act, 1959 (38 of 1959), or a corresponding new bank`
  line `constituted under section 3 of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings)`
  line `Act, 1970 (5 of 1970), or under section 3 of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of`
  line `Undertakings) Act, 1980 (40 of 1980), or any other bank, being a bank included in the Second`
  line `Schedule to the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);]`
  line `1 [( xxii ) as subscription to such bonds issued by the National Bank for Agriculture and Rural`
  line `Development, as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this`
  line behalf;]
  line `2 [( xxiii ) in an account under the Senior Citizens Savings Scheme Rules, 2004;`
  line `( xxiv ) as five year time deposit in an account under the Post Office Time Deposit Rules, 1981.]`
  line `( 3 ) The provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) shall apply only to so much of any premium or other payment`
  line `made on an 3 [insurance policy, other than a contract for a deferred annuity, issued on or before the 31st`
  line `day of March, 2012,] as is not in excess of twenty per cent of the actual capital sum assured.`
  line `Explanation. — In calculating any such actual capital sum assured, no account shall be taken —`
  line `( i ) of the value of any premiums agreed to be returned, or`
  line `( ii ) of any benefit by way of bonus or otherwise over and above the sum actually assured, which`
  line `is to be or may be received under the policy by any person.`
  line `4 [( 3A ) The provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) shall apply only to so much of any premium or other`
  line `payment made on an insurance policy, other than a contract for a deferred annuity, issued on or after the`
  line `1st day of April, 2012 as is not in excess of ten per cent of the actual capital sum assured:`
  line `5 [Provided that where the policy, issued on or after the 1st day of April, 2013, is for insurance on life`
  line `of any person, who is —`
  line `( a ) a person with disability or a person with severe disability as referred to in section 80U, or`
  line `( b ) suffering from disease or ailment as specified in the rules made under section 80DDB,`
  line `the provisions of this sub- section shall have effect as if for the words “ten per cent.”, the words “fifteen`
  line `per cent.” had been substituted.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- section, “actual capital sum assured” in relation to a life`
  line `insurance policy shall mean the minimum amount assured under the policy on happening of the insured`
  line `event at any time during the term of the policy, not taking into account —`
  line `( i ) the value of any premium agreed to be returned; or`
  line `( ii ) any benefit by way of bonus or otherwise over and above the sum actually assured, which is`
  line `to be or may be received under the policy by any person.]`
  line `( 4 ) The persons referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) shall be the following, namely: —`
  line `( a ) for the purposes of clauses ( i ), ( v ), ( x ) and ( xi ) of that sub-section, —`
  line `( i ) in the case of an individual, the individual, the wife or husband and any child of such`
  line `individual, and`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 24, for “insurance policy other than a contract for a deferred annuity” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 24, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
