obj_root_law_sections_334_content:
  string
  line 334
  line `( ii ) in the case of a Hindu undivided family, any member thereof;`
  line `( b ) for the purposes of clause ( ii ) of that sub-section, in the case of an individual, the individual,`
  line `the wife or husband and any child of such individual;`
  line `1 [( ba ) for the purposes of clause ( viii ) of that sub-section, in the case of an individual, the`
  line `individual or any girl child of that individual, or any girl child for whom such person is the legal`
  line `guardian, if the scheme so specifies;]`
  line `( c ) for the purposes of clause ( xvii ) of that sub-section, in the case of an individual, any two`
  line `children of such individual.`
  line `( 5 ) Where, in any previous year, an assessee —`
  line `( i ) terminates his contract of insurance referred to in clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 2 ), by notice to that`
  line `effect or where the contract ceases to be in force by reason of failure to pay any premium, by not`
  line `reviving contract of insurance, —`
  line `( a ) in case of any single premium policy, within two years after the date of commencement of`
  line `insurance; or`
  line `( b ) in any other case, before premiums have been paid for two years; or`
  line `( ii ) terminates his participation in any unit-linked insurance plan referred to in clause ( x ) or`
  line `clause ( xi ) of sub-section ( 2 ), by notice to that effect or where he ceases to participate by reason of`
  line `failure to pay any contribution, by not reviving his participation, before contributions in respect of`
  line `such participation have been paid for five years; or`
  line `( iii ) transfers the house property referred to in clause ( xviii ) of sub-section ( 2 ) before the expiry of`
  line `five years from the end of the financial year in which possession of such property is obtained by him,`
  line `or receives back, whether by way of refund or otherwise, any sum specified in that clause,`
  line `then, —`
  line `( a ) no deduction shall be allowed to the assessee under sub-section ( 1 ) with reference to any of`
  line `the sums, referred to in clauses ( i ), ( x ), ( xi ) and ( xviii ) of sub-section ( 2 ), paid in such previous year;`
  line and
  line `( b ) the aggregate amount of the deductions of income so allowed in respect of the previous year`
  line `or years preceding such previous year, shall be deemed to be the income of the assessee of such`
  line `previous year and shall be liable to tax in the assessment year relevant to such previous year.`
  line `( 6 ) If any equity shares or debentures, with reference to the cost of which a deduction is allowed`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ), are sold or otherwise transferred by the assessee to any person at any time within a`
  line `period of three years from the date of their acquisition, the aggregate amount of the deductions of income`
  line `so allowed in respect of such equity shares or debentures in the previous year or years preceding the`
  line `previous year in which such sale or transfer has taken place shall be deemed to be the income of the`
  line `assessee of such previous year and shall be liable to tax in the assessment year relevant to such previous`
  line year.
  line `Explanation. — A person shall be treated as having acquired any shares or debentures on the date on`
  line `which his name is entered in relation to those shares or debentures in the register of members or of`
  line `debenture-holders, as the case may be, of the public company.`
  line `2 [( 6A ) If any amount, including interest accrued thereon, is withdrawn by the assessee from his`
  line `account referred to in clause ( xxiii ) or clause ( xxiv ) of sub-section ( 2 ), before the expiry of the period of`
  line `five years from the date of its deposit, the amount so withdrawn shall be deemed to be the income of the`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_334_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_335:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-335
  sectionNo (335)
  orderNo 335
  title `Page 335`
  content obj_root_law_sections_335_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_335_footnotes
  sourcePage 335
obj_root_law_sections_335_content:
  string
  line 335
  line `assessee of the previous year in which the amount is withdrawn and shall be liable to tax in the`
  line `assessment year relevant to such previous year:`
  line `Provided that the amount liable to tax shall not include the following amounts, namely: —`
  line `( i ) any amount of interest, relating to deposits referred to in clause ( xxiii ) or clause ( xxiv ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ), which has been included in the total income of the assessee of the previous year or`
  line `years preceding such previous year; and`
  line `( ii ) any amount received by the nominee or legal heir of the assessee, on the death of such`
  line `assessee, other than interest, if any, accrued thereon, which was not included in the total income of`
  line `the assessee for the previous year or years preceding such previous year.]`
  line `( 7 ) For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) the insurance, deferred annuity, provident fund and superannuation fund referred to in`
  line `clauses ( i ) to ( vii );`
  line `( b ) unit-linked insurance plan and annuity plan referred to in clauses ( xii ) to ( xiiia );`
  line `( c ) pension fund and subscription to deposit scheme referred to in clauses ( xiiic ) to ( xiva );`
  line `( d ) amount borrowed for purchase or construction of a residential house referred to in clause ( xv ),`
  line `of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 88 shall be eligible for deduction under the corresponding provisions of this`
  line `section and the deduction shall be allowed in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line `( 8 ) In this section, —`
  line `( i ) “Administrator” means the Administrator as referred to in clause ( a ) of section 2 of the Unit`
  line `Trust of India (Transfer of Undertaking and Repeal) Act, 2002 (58 of 2002);`
  line `( ii ) “contribution” to any fund shall not include any sums in repayment of loan;`
  line `( iii ) “insurance” shall include—`
  line `( a ) a policy of insurance on the life of an individual or the spouse or the child of such`
  line `individual or a member of a Hindu undivided family securing the payment of specified sum on`
  line `the stipulated date of maturity, if such person is alive on such date notwithstanding that the policy`
  line `of insurance provides only for the return of premiums paid (with or without any interest thereon)`
  line `in the event of such person dying before the said stipulated date;`
  line `( b ) a policy of insurance effected by an individual or a member of a Hindu undivided family`
  line `for the benefit of a minor with the object of enabling the minor, after he has attained majority to`
  line `secure insurance on his own life by adopting the policy and on his being alive on a date (after`
  line `such adoption) specified in the policy in this behalf;`
  line `( iv ) “Life Insurance Corporation” means the Life In surance Corporation of India established`
  line `under the Life Insurance Corporation Act, 1956 (31 of 1956);`
  line `( v ) “public company” shall have the same meaning as in section 3 of the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line `( vi ) “security” means a Government security as defined in clause ( 2 ) of section 2 of the Public`
  line `Debt Act, 1944 (18 of 1944);`
  line `( vii ) “specified company” means a company as referred to in clause ( h ) of section 2 of the Unit`
  line `Trust of India (Transfer of Undertaking and Repeal) Act, 2002 (58 of 2002);`
  line `( viii ) “transfer” shall be deemed to include also the transactions referred to in clause ( f ) of`
  line `section 269UA.]`
