obj_root_law_sections_336_content:
  string
  line 336
  line `80CC. [ Deduction in respect of investment in certain new shares ]. — Omitted by the`
  line `Finance ( No. 2) Act, 1996 (33 of 1996), s. 22 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `1 [80CCA. Deduction in respect of deposits under National Savings Scheme or payment to a`
  line `deferred annuity plan. — ( 1 ) Where an assessee, being —`
  line `( a ) an individual, or`
  line `( b ) a Hindu undivided family, 2 ***`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `has in the previous year —`
  line `( i ) deposited any amount in accordance with such scheme as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf 4 ***; or`
  line `( ii ) paid any amount to effect or to keep in force a contract for such annuity plan of the Life`
  line `Insurance Corporation as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line specify,
  line `out of his income chargeable to tax, he shall, in accordance with, and subject to, the provisions of this`
  line `section, be allowed a deduction in the computation of his total income of the whole of the amount`
  line `deposited or paid (excluding interest or bonus accrued or credited to the assessee’s account, if any) as`
  line `does not exceed the amount of twenty thousand rupees in the previous year:`
  line `5 [ Provided that in relation to —`
  line `( a ) the assessment years commencing on the 1st day of April, 1989 and the 1st day of April,`
  line `1990, this sub- section shall have effect as if for the words “twenty thousand rupees”, the words`
  line `“thirty thousand rupees” had been substituted;`
  line `( b ) the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1991 and subsequent assessment`
  line `years, this sub- section shall have effect as if for the words “twenty thousand rupees”, the words “forty`
  line `thousand rupees” had been s ubstituted:]`
  line `6 [Provided further that no deduction under this sub-section shall be allowed in relation to any`
  line `amount deposited or paid under clauses ( i ) and ( ii ) on or after the 1st day of April, 1992.]`
  line `( 2 ) Where any amount —`
  line `( a ) standing to the credit of the assessee 7 [under the scheme referred to in clause ( i ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 )] in respect of which a deduction has been allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) together with`
  line `the interest accrued on such amount is withdrawn in whole or in part in any previous year, or`
  line `( b ) is received on account of the surrender of the policy or as annuity or bonus in accordance with`
  line `the annuity plan of the Life Insurance Corporation in any previous year,`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 23, for section 80CCA (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. The words “or” omitted by Act 32 of 1994, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988.)`
  line `3. Clause ( c ) omitted by s. 50, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `4. The brackets and words “(hereafter in this section referred to as the National Savings Scheme)” omitted by`
  line `Act 49 of 1991, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 16, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 25, for “under the National Savings Scheme” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_336_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_337:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-337
  sectionNo (337)
  orderNo 337
  title `Page 337`
  content obj_root_law_sections_337_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_337_footnotes
  sourcePage 337
obj_root_law_sections_337_content:
  string
  line 337
  line `an amount equal to the whole of the amount referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) shall be deemed to be`
  line `the income of the assessee of that previous year in which such withdrawal is made or, as the case may be,`
  line `amount is received, and shall, accordingly, be chargeable to tax as the income of that previous year:`
  line `1 [Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply to any amount received by the`
  line `assessee on account of the surrender of the policy in accordance with the terms of the annuity plan of the`
  line `Life Insurance Corporation where the assessee elects to surrender before the 1st day of October, 1992, the`
  line `said annuity plan in respect of which he had paid any amount under clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) before`
  line `the 1st day of April, 1992.]`
  line `2 [( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, where a partition has`
  line `taken place among the members of a Hindu undivided family or where an association of persons has been`
  line `dissolved after a deduction has been allowed under sub-section ( 1 ), the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) shall`
  line `apply as if the person in receipt of income referred to therein is the assessee.]`
  line `Explanation I. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that interest on the deposits made`
  line `3 [under the scheme referred to in clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 )] shall not be chargeable to tax except in the`
  line `manner and to the extent specified in sub-section ( 2 ).`
  line `Explanation II. —For the purposes of this section, “Life Insurance Corporation” shall have the same`
  line `meaning as in clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 8 ) of section 80C.`
  line `4 [ 80CCB. Deduction in respect of investment made under Equity Linked Savings Scheme. — ( 1 )`
  line `Where an assessee, being —`
  line `( a ) an individual, or`
  line `( b ) a Hindu undivided family, 5 ***`
  line `6 * * * * *`
  line `has acquired in the previous year, out of his income chargeable to tax, units of any Mutual Fund specified`
  line `under clause (23D) of section 10 or of the Unit Trust of India established under the Unit Trust of India`
  line `Act, 1963 (52 of 1963), under any plan formulated in accordance with such scheme as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf (hereafter in this section`
  line `referred to as the Equity Linked Savings Scheme), he shall, in accordance with, and subject to, the`
  line `provisions of this section, be allowed a deduction in the computation of his total income of so much of the`
  line `amount invested as does not exceed the amount of ten thousand rupees in the previous year:`
  line `7 [Provided that no deduction shall be allowed in relation to any amount invested under this`
  line `sub-section on or after the 1st day of April, 1992.]`
  line `( 2 ) Where any amount invested by the assessee in the units issued under a plan formulated under the`
  line `Equity Linked Savings Scheme in respect of which a deduction has been allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) is`
  line `returned to him in whole or in part either by way of repurchase of such units or on the termination of the`
  line `plan, by the Fund or the Trust, as the case may be, in any previous year, it shall be deemed to be the`
  line `income of the assessee of that previous year and chargeable to tax accordingly.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 25, for “under the National Savings Scheme” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1991)`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `5. The word “or” omitted by Act 32 of 1994, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1991.)`
  line `6. Clause ( c ) omitted by s. 50, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 43 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
