obj_root_law_sections_338_content:
  string
  line 338
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, where a partition has taken`
  line `place among the members of a Hindu undivided family or where an association of persons has been`
  line `dissolved after a deduction has been allowed under sub-section ( 1 ), the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) shall`
  line `apply as if the person in receipt of income referred to therein is the assessee.]`
  line `1 [ 80CCC. Deduction in respect of contribution to certain pension funds. — ( 1 ) Where an assessee`
  line `being an individual has in the previous year paid or deposited any amount out of his income chargeable to`
  line `tax to effect or keep in force a contract for any annuity plan of Life Insurance Corporation of India 2 [or`
  line `any other insurer] for receiving pension from the fund referred to in clause ( 23AAB ) of section 10, he`
  line `shall, in accordance with, and subject to, the provisions of this section, be allowed a deduction in the`
  line `computation of his total income, of the whole of the amount paid or deposited (excluding interest or`
  line `bonus accrued or credited to the assessee’s account, if any) as does not exceed the amount of 3 [one`
  line `hundred and fifty thousand rupees] in the previous year.`
  line `( 2 ) Where any amount standing to the credit of the assessee in a fund, referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) in`
  line `respect of which a deduction has been allowed under sub-section ( 1 ), together with the interest or bonus`
  line `accrued or credited to the assessee’s account, if any, is received by the assessee or his nominee—`
  line `( a ) on account of the surrender of the annuity plan whether in whole or in part, in any previous`
  line `year, or`
  line `( b ) as pension received from the annuity plan,`
  line `an amount equal to the whole of the amount referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) shall be deemed to be`
  line `the income of the assessee or his nominee, as the case may be, in that previous year in which such`
  line `withdrawal is made or, as the case may be, pension is received, and shall accordingly be chargeable to tax`
  line `as income of that previous year.`
  line `4 [( 3 ) Where any amount paid or deposited by the assessee has been taken into account for the`
  line `purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) a rebate with reference to such amount shall not be allowed under section 88 for any`
  line `assessment year ending before the 1st day of April, 2006;`
  line `( b ) a deduction with reference to such amount shall not be allowed under section 80C for any`
  line `assessment year beginning on or after the 1st day of April, 2006.]]`
  line `5 [ 80CCD. Deduction in respect of contribution to pension scheme of Central Government. — ( 1 )`
  line `6 [Where an assessee, being an individual employed by the Central Government on or after the 1st day of`
  line `January, 2004 or, being an individual employed by any other employer], 7 [or any other assessee, being an`
  line `individual] has in the previous year paid or deposited any amount in his account under a pension scheme`
  line `notified or as may be notified by the Central Government, he shall, in accordance with, and subject to, the`
  line `provisions of this section, be allowed a deduction in the computation of his total income, of the whole of`
  line `the amount so paid or deposited 8 [as does not exceed, —`
  line `( a ) in the case of an employee, ten per cent of his salary in the previous year; and`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 23 (w.e..f 1-4-1997).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 17, for “one lakh rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2016).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 22, for sub-section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 28, for “Where an assessee, being an individual employed by the Central Government or any`
  line `other employer on or after the 1st day of January, 2004” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2015).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 30, ibid., for “as does not exceed ten per cent. of his salary in the previous year” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2009).`
