  sourcePage 339
obj_root_law_sections_339_content:
  string
  line 339
  line `( b ) in any other case, 1 [twenty per cent.] of his gross total income in the previous year.]`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `3 [( 1B ) An assessee referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), shall be allowed a deduction in computation of his`
  line `total income, whether or not any deductions is allowed under sub-section ( 1 ), of the whole of the amount`
  line `paid or deposited in the previous year in his account under a pension scheme notified or as may be`
  line `notified by the Central Government, which shall not exceed fifty thousand rupees:`
  line `Provided that no deduction under this sub-section shall be allowed in respect of the amount on which`
  line `a deduction has been claimed and allowed under sub-section ( 1 ).]`
  line `( 2 ) Where, in the case of an assessee referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), the 4 [Central Government or any`
  line `other employer] makes any contribution to his account referred to in that sub-section, the assessee shall be`
  line `allowed a deduction in the computation of his total income, of the whole of the amount contributed by the`
  line `4 [Central Government or any other employer] as does not exceed ten per cent of his salary in the previous`
  line year.
  line `( 3 ) Where any amount standing to the credit of the assessee in his account referred to in`
  line `5 [sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 1B )], in respect of which a deduction has been allowed 6 [under those`
  line `sub-sections] or sub-section ( 2 ), together with the amount accrued thereon, if any, is received by the`
  line `assessee or his nominee, in whole or in part, in any previous year, —`
  line `( a ) on account of closure or his opting out of the pension scheme referred to in`
  line `5 [sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 1B )]; or`
  line `( b ) as pension received from the annuity plan purchased or taken on such closure or opting out,`
  line `the whole of the amount referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) shall be deemed to be the income of the`
  line `assessee or his nominee, as the case may be, in the previous year in which such amount is received, and`
  line `shall accordingly be charged to tax as income of that previous year.`
  line `7 [Provided that the amount received by the nominee, on the death of the assessee, under the`
  line `circumstances referred to in clause ( a ), shall not be deemed to be the income of the nominee.]`
  line `8 [( 4 ) Where any amount paid or deposited by the assessee has been allowed as a deduction under`
  line `5 [sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 1B )], —`
  line `( a ) no rebate with reference to such amount shall be allowed under section 88 for any assessment`
  line `year ending before the 1st day of April, 2006;`
  line `( b ) no deduction with reference to such amount shall be allowed under section 80C for any`
  line `assessment year beginning on or after the 1st day of April, 2006.]`
  line `9 [( 5 ) For the purposes of this section, the assessee shall be deemed not to have received any amount in`
  line `the previous year if such amount is used for purchasing an annuity plan in the same previous year.]`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, “salary” includes d earness allowance, if the terms of`
  line `employment so provide, but excludes all other allowances and perquisites.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 33 for “ten per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2018).`
  line `2. Sub-section ( 1A ) omitted by Act 20 of 2015, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 18, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 25, for “Central Government” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2004).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 18, for “sub -section ( 1 )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2016).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for “ under that sub - section” (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 23, for sub-section ( 4 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
