obj_root_law_sections_340_content:
  string
  line 340
  line `1 [ 80CCE. Limit on deductions under section 80C, section 80CCC and 80CCD. — The aggregate`
  line `amount of deductions under section 80C, section 80CCC and 2 [sub-section ( 1 ) of section 80CCD] shall`
  line `not, in any case, exceed 3 [one hundred and fifty thousand rupees].]`
  line `4 [ 80CCF. Deduction in respect of subscription to long-term infrastructure bonds. — In computing`
  line `the total income of an assessee, being an individual or a Hindu undivided family, there shall be deducted,`
  line `the whole of the amount, to the extent such amount does not exceed twenty thousand rupees, paid or`
  line `deposited, during the previous year relevant to the assessment year beginning on the 1st day`
  line `of April, 2011 5 [or to the assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2012], as subscription to`
  line `long-term infrastructure bonds as may, for the purposes of this section, be notified by the Central`
  line Government.]
  line `6 [ 80CCG. Deduction in respect of investment made under an equity savings scheme. — ( 1 ) Where`
  line `an assessee, being a resident individual, has, in a previous year, acquired listed equity shares 7 [or listed`
  line `units of an equity oriented fund] in accordance with a scheme, as may be notified by the Central`
  line `Government in this behalf, he shall, subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 3 ), be allowed a deduction,`
  line `in the computation of his total income of the assessment year relevant to such previous year, of fifty per`
  line `cent of the amount invested in such equity shares 7 [or units] to the extent such deduction does not exceed`
  line `twenty-five thousand rupees.`
  line `8 [( 2 ) The deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be allowed in accordance with, and subject to, the`
  line `provisions of this section for three consecutive assessment years, beginning with the assessment year`
  line `relevant to the previous year in which the listed equity shares or listed units of equity oriented fund were`
  line `first acquired.]`
  line `( 3 ) The deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be subject to the following conditions, namely: —`
  line `( i ) the gross total income of the assessee for the relevant assessment year shall not exceed`
  line `9 [twelve lakh rupees];`
  line `( ii ) the assessee is a new retail investor as may be specified under the scheme referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 );`
  line `( iii ) the investment is made in such listed equity shares 7 [or listed units of equity oriented fund] as`
  line `may be specified under the scheme referred to in sub-section ( 1 );`
  line `( iv ) the investment is locked-in for a period of three years from the date of acquisition in`
  line `accordance with the scheme referred to in sub-section ( 1 ); and`
  line `( v ) such other condition as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 4 ) If the assessee, in any previous year, fails to comply with any condition specified in`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ), the deduction originally allowed shall be deemed to be the income of the assessee of such`
  line `previous year and shall be liable to tax for the assessment year relevant to such previous year.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 9, for “section 80CCD” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2012).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 29, for “one lakh rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2015).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-2011).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-2012).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for sub-section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
  line `9. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for “ten lakh rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_340_footnotes:
