  title `Page 341`
  content obj_root_law_sections_341_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_341_footnotes
  sourcePage 341
obj_root_law_sections_341_content:
  string
  line 341
  line `1 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, “equity oriented fund” shall have the meaning`
  line `assigned to it in the Explanation to clause ( 38 ) of section 10.]`
  line `2 [( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections ( 1 ) to ( 4 ), no deduction under this section`
  line `shall be allowed in respect of any assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 2018:`
  line `Provided that an assessee, who has acquired listed equity shares or listed units of an equity oriented`
  line `fund in accordance with the scheme referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) and claimed deduction under this`
  line `section for any assessment year commencing on or before the 1st day of April, 2017, shall be allowed`
  line `deduction under this section till the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 2019, if he is`
  line `otherwise eligible to claim the deduction in accordance with the other provisions of this section.]`
  line `3 [ 80D. Deduction in respect of health insurance premia. — ( 1 ) In computing the total income of an`
  line `assessee, being an individual or a Hindu undivided family, there shall be deducted such sum, as specified`
  line `in sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-section ( 3 ), payment of which is made by any mode 4 [as specified in sub-section`
  line `( 2B )], in the previous year out of his income chargeable to tax.`
  line `( 2 ) Where the assessee is an individual, the sum referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be the aggregate`
  line `of the following, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the whole of the amount paid to effect or to keep in force an insurance on the health of the`
  line `assessee or his family 5 [or any contribution made to the Central Government Health Scheme] 6 [or`
  line `such other scheme as may be notified by the Central Government in this behalf] 7 [or any payment`
  line `made on account of preventive health check-up of the assessee or his family] as does not exceed in`
  line `the aggregate 8 [twenty-five thousand rupees]; and`
  line `( b ) the whole of the amount paid to effect or to keep in force an insurance on the health of the`
  line `parents or parents of the assessee 7 [or any payment made on account of preventive health check-up of`
  line `the parent or parents of the assessee] as does not exceed in the aggregate 8 [twenty-five thousand`
  line rupees];
  line `9 [( c ) the whole of the amount paid on account of medical expenditure incurred on the health of`
  line `the assessee or any member of his family as does not exceed in the aggregate 10 [fifty thousand`
  line `rupees]; and`
  line `( d ) the whole of the amount paid on account of medical expenditure incurred on the health of any`
  line `parent of the assessee, as does not exceed in the aggregate 10 [fifty thousand rupees]:`
  line `Provided that the amount referred to in clause ( c ) or clause ( d ) is paid in respect of a 11 *** senior`
  line `citizen and no amount has been paid to effect or to keep in force an insurance on the health of such`
  line `person:`
  line `Provided further that the aggregate of the sum specified under clause ( a ) and clause ( c ) or the`
  line `aggregate of the sum specified under clause ( b ) and clause ( d ) shall not exceed 10 [fifty thousand`
  line rupees].]
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of clause ( a ), “family” means the spouse and dependant children of`
  line `the assessee.`
  line `7 [( 2A ) Where the amounts referred to in clauses ( a ) and ( b ) of sub-section ( 2 ) are paid on account of`
  line `preventive health check-up, the deduction for such amounts shall be allowed to the extent it does not`
  line `exceed in the aggregate five thousand rupees.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 17, for section 80D (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 26, for “, other than cash,” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-4-2011).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 20 of 2 015, s. 19, for “fifteen thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2016).`
  line `9. Ins. by s. 19, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 26, for “thirty thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2019).`
  line `11. The word “very” omitted by s. 26, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_341_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_342:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-342
  sectionNo (342)
  orderNo 342
  title `Page 342`
  content obj_root_law_sections_342_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_342_footnotes
  sourcePage 342
obj_root_law_sections_342_content:
  string
  line 342
  line `( 2B ) For the purposes of deduction under sub-section ( 1 ), the payment shall be made by —`
  line `( i ) any mode, including cash, in respect of any sum paid on account of preventive health`
  line check-up;
  line `( ii ) any mode other than cash in all other cases not falling under clause ( i ).]`
  line `1 [( 3 ) Where the assessee is a Hindu undivided family, the sum referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), shall be`
  line `the aggregate of the following, namely: —`
  line `( a ) whole of the amount paid to effect or to keep in force an insurance on the health of any`
  line `member of that Hindu undivided family as does not exceed in the aggregate twenty-five thousand`
  line `rupees; and`
  line `( b ) the whole of the amount paid on account of medical expenditure incurred on the health of any`
  line `member of the Hindu undivided family as does not exceed in the aggregate 2 [fifty thousand rupees]:`
  line `Provided that the amount referred to in clause ( b ) is paid in respect of a 3 *** senior citizen and no`
  line `amount has been paid to effect or to keep in force an insurance on the health of such person:`
  line `Provided further that the aggregate of the sum specified under clause ( a ) and clause ( b ) shall not`
  line `exceed 2 [fifty thousand rupees].]`
  line `( 4 ) Where the sum specified in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 2 ) 4 [or clause ( a ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 3 )] is paid to effect or keep in force an insurance on the health of any person specified`
  line `therein, and who is a senior citizen, 5 ***, the provisions of this section shall have effect as if for the`
  line `words 6 [twenty-five thousand rupees], the words 7 [fifty thousand rupees] had been substituted.`
  line `8 * * * * *`
  line `9 [( 4A ) Where the amount specified in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 2 ) or clause ( a ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ) is paid in lump sum in the previous year to effect or to keep in force an insurance on the`
  line `health of any person specified therein for more than a year, then, subject to the provisions of this section,`
  line `there shall be allowed for each of the relevant previous year, a deduction equal to the appropriate fraction`
  line `of the amount.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, —`
  line `( i ) “appropriate fraction” means the fraction, the numerator of which is one and the denominator`
  line `of which is the total number of relevant previous years;`
  line `( ii ) “relevant previous year” means the previous year beginning with the previous year in which`
  line `such amount is paid and the subsequent previous year or years during which the insurance shall have`
  line `effect or be in force. ]`
  line `( 5 ) The insurance referred to in this section shall be in accordance with a scheme made in this behalf`
  line `by —`
  line `( a ) the General Insurance Corporation of India formed under section 9 of the General Insurance`
  line `Business (Nationalisation) Act, 1972 (57 of 1972) and approved by the Central Government in this`
  line `behalf; or`
  line `( b ) any other insurer and approved by the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority`
  line `established under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 3 of the Insurance Regulatory and Development`
  line `Authority Act, 1999 (41 of 1999).]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 19, for sub-section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 26, for “thirty thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2019).`
  line `3. The word “very” omitted by s. 26 (w.e.f. 1 -4-2019).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 19, for “or in sub -section ( 3 )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2016).`
  line `5. The words “ or a very senior citizen ” omitted by Act 13 o f 2018, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019) which was earlier inserted by`
  line `Act 20 of 2015, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 19, ibid., for “fifteen thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2016).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 26, for “thirty thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2019). Earlier it was substituted by s. 19, ibid., for`
  line `“twenty thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2016).`
  line `8. Explanation omitted by Act 20 of 2015, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
