obj_root_law_sections_343_content:
  string
  line 343
  line `1 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) ”senior citizen” means an individual resident in India who is of the age of sixty years or more`
  line `at any time during the relevant previous year;`
  line `2 * * * * *]`
  line `3 [ 80DD. Deduction in respect of maintenance including medical treatment of a dependant who`
  line `is a person with disability. — 4 [( 1 ) Where an assessee, being an individual or a Hindu undivided family,`
  line `who is a resident in India, has, during the previous year, —`
  line `( a ) incurred any expenditure for the medical treatment (including nursing), training and`
  line `rehabilitation of a dependant, being a person with disability; or`
  line `( b ) paid or deposited any amount under a scheme framed in this behalf by the Life Insurance`
  line `Corporation or any other insurer or the Administrator or the specified company subject to the`
  line `conditions specified in sub-section ( 2 ) and approved by the Board in this behalf for the maintenance`
  line `of a dependant, being a person with disability,`
  line `the assessee shall, in accordance with and subject to the provisions of this section, be allowed a deduction`
  line `of a sum of seventy-five thousand rupees from his gross total income in respect of the previous year:`
  line `Provided that where such dependant is a person with severe disability, the provisions of this`
  line `sub- section shall have effect as if for the words “seventy - five thousand rupees”, the words “one hundred`
  line `and twenty- five thousand rupees” had been substituted. ]`
  line `( 2 ) The deduction under clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) shall be allowed only if the following conditions`
  line `are fulfilled, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the scheme referred to in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) provides for payment of annuity or`
  line `lump sum amount for the benefit of a dependant, being a person with disability, in the event of the`
  line `death of the individual or the member of the Hindu undivided family in whose name subscription to`
  line `the scheme has been made;`
  line `( b ) the assessee nominates either the dependant, being a person with disability, or any other`
  line `person or a trust to receive the payment on his behalf, for the benefit of the dependant, being a person`
  line `with disability.`
  line `( 3 ) If the dependant, being a person with disability, predeceases the individual or the member of the`
  line `Hindu undivided family referred to in sub-section ( 2 ), an amount equal to the amount paid or deposited`
  line `under clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to be the income of the assessee of the previous year`
  line `in which such amount is received by the assessee and shall accordingly be chargeable to tax as the income`
  line `of that previous year.`
  line `( 4 ) The assessee, claiming a deduction under this section, shall furnish a copy of the certificate issued`
  line `by the medical authority in the prescribed form and manner, along with the return of income under`
  line `section 139, in respect of the assessment year for which the deduction is claimed:`
  line `Provided that where the condition of disability requires reassessment of its extent after a period`
  line `stipulated in the aforesaid certificate, no deduction under this section shall be allowed for any assessment`
  line `year relating to any previous year beginning after the expiry of the previous year during which the`
  line `aforesaid certificate of disability had expired, unless a new certificate is obtained from the medical`
  line `authority in the form and manner, as may be prescribed, and a copy thereof is furnished along with the`
  line `return of income.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `2. Clause ( ii ) omitted by Act 13 of 2018, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 34, for section 80DD (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 20, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
