obj_root_law_sections_344_content:
  string
  line 344
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “Administrator” means the Administrator as referred to in clause ( a ) of section 2 of the Unit`
  line `Trust of India (Transfer of Undertaking and Repeal) Act, 2002 (58 of 2002);`
  line `( b ) “dependant” means—`
  line `( i ) in the case of an individual, the spouse, children, parents, brothers and sisters of the`
  line `individual or any of them;`
  line `( ii ) in the case of a Hindu undivided family, a member of the Hindu undivided family,`
  line `dependant wholly or mainly on such individual or Hindu undivided family for his support and`
  line `maintenance, and who has not claimed any deduction under section 80U in computing his total income`
  line `for the assessment year relating to the previous year;`
  line `( c ) “disability” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( i ) of section 2 of the Persons with`
  line `Disabilities (Equal Opportunities, Protection of Rights and Full Participation) Act, 1995 (1 of 1996)`
  line `1 [and includes “autism”, “cerebral palsy” and “multiple disability” referred to in clauses ( a ), ( c ) and`
  line `( h ) of section 2 of the National Trust for Welfare of Persons with Autism, Cerebral Palsy, Mental`
  line `Retardation and Multiple Disabilities Act, 1999 (44 of 1999)];`
  line `( d ) “Life Insurance Corporation” shall have the same meaning as in clause ( iii ) of sub-section ( 8 )`
  line `of section 88;`
  line `( e ) “medical authority” means the medical authority as referred to in clause ( p ) of section 2 of the`
  line `Persons with Disabilities (Equal Opportunities, Protection of Rights and Full Participation)`
  line `Act, 1995 (1 of 1996) 1 [or such other medical authority as may, by notification, be specified by the`
  line `Central Government for certifying “autism”, “cerebral palsy”, “multiple disabilities”, “p erson with`
  line `disability” and “severe disability” referred to in clauses ( a ), ( c ), ( h ), ( j ) and ( o ) of section 2 of the`
  line `National Trust for Welfare of Persons with Autism, Cerebral Palsy, Mental Retardation and Multiple`
  line `Disabilities Act, 1999 (44 of 1999)];`
  line `( f ) “person with disability” means a person as referred to in clause ( t) of section 2 of the`
  line `Persons with Disabilities (Equal Opportunities, Protection of Rights and Full Participation)`
  line `Act, 1995 (1 of 1996) 1 [or clause ( j ) of section 2 of the National Trust for Welfare of Persons with`
  line `Autism, Cerebral Palsy, Mental Retardation and Multiple Disabilities Act, 1999 (44 of 1999)];`
  line `2 [( g ) “person with severe disability” means—`
  line `( i ) a person with eighty per cent or more of one or more disabilities, as referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 4 ) of section 56 of the Persons with Disabilities (Equal Opportunities, Protection of`
  line `Rights and Full Participation) Act, 1995 (1 of 1996); or`
  line `( ii ) a person with severe disability referred to in clause ( o ) of section 2 of the National Trust`
  line `for Welfare of Persons with Autism, Cerebral Palsy, Mental Retardation and Multiple Disabilities`
  line `Act, 1999 (44 of 1999);]`
  line `( h ) “specified company” means a company as referred to in clause ( h ) of section 2 of the Unit`
  line `Trust of India (Transfer of Undertaking and Repeal) Act, 2002 (58 of 2002).]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for clause ( g ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
