obj_root_law_sections_345_content:
  string
  line 345
  line `1 [80DDB. Deduction in respect of medical treatment, etc. — Where an assessee who is resident in`
  line `India has, during the previous year, actually paid any amount for the medical treatment of such disease or`
  line `ailment as may be specified in the rules made in this behalf by the Board —`
  line `( a ) for himself or a dependant, in case the assessee is an individual; or`
  line `( b ) for any member of a Hindu undivided family, in case the assessee is a Hindu undivided`
  line family,
  line `the assessee shall be allowed a deduction of the amount actually paid or a sum of forty thousand rupees,`
  line `whichever is less, in respect of that previous year in which such amount was actually paid:`
  line `2 [Provided that no such deduction shall be allowed unless the assessee obtains the prescription for`
  line `such medical treatment from a neurologist, an oncologist, a urologist, a haematologist, an immunologist`
  line `or such other specialist, as may be prescribed:]`
  line `Provided further that the deduction under this section shall be reduced by the amount received, if any,`
  line `under an insurance from an insurer, or reimbursed by an employer, for the medical treatment of the`
  line `person referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ):`
  line `Provided also that where the amount actually paid is in respect of the assessee or his dependant or any`
  line `member of a Hindu undivided family of the assessee and who is a senior citizen, the provisions of this`
  line `section shall have effect as if for the words “forty thousand rupees”, the words “ 3 [one hundred thousand`
  line `rupees] ” had been substituted:`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “dependant” means—`
  line `( a ) in the case of an individual, the spouse, children, parents, brothers and sisters of the`
  line `individual or any of them,`
  line `( b ) in the case of a Hindu undivided family, a member of the Hindu undivided family,`
  line `dependant wholly or mainly on such individual or Hindu undivided family for his support and`
  line maintenance;
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 35, for section 80DDB (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 21, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 27, for “sixty thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2019).`
  line `4. The fourth proviso omitted by s. 27, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2019). Earlier it was inserted by Act 20 of 2015,`
  line `s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
