obj_root_law_sections_346_content:
  string
  line 346
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `( iii ) “insurer” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( 9 ) of section 2 of the Insurance Act,`
  line `1938 (4 of 1938);`
  line `( iv ) “senior citizen” means an individual resident in India who is of the age of 2 [sixty years] or`
  line `more at any time during the relevant previous year;]`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 [80E. Deduction in respect of interest on loan taken for higher education. — ( 1 ) In computing the`
  line `total income of an assessee, being an individual, there shall be deducted, in accordance with and subject`
  line `to the provisions of this section, any amount paid by him in the previous year, out of his income`
  line `chargeable to tax, by way of interest on loan taken by him from any financial institution or any approved`
  line `charitable institution for the purpose of pursuing his higher education 5 [or for the purpose of higher`
  line `education of his relative].`
  line `( 2 ) The deduction specified in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be allowed in computing the total income in`
  line `respect of the initial assessment year and seven assessment years immediately succeeding the initial`
  line `assessment year or until the interest referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) is paid by the assessee in full, whichever`
  line `is earlier.`
  line `( 3 ) For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “approved charitable institution” means an institution specified in, or, as the case may be, an`
  line `institution established for charitable purposes and 6 [approved by the prescribed authority] under`
  line `clause ( 23C ) of section 10 or an institution referred to in clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 80G;`
  line `( b ) “financial institution” means a banking company to which the Banking Regu lation`
  line `Act, 1949 (10 of 1949) applies (including any bank or banking institution referred to in section 51 of`
  line `that Act); or any other financial institution which the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, specify in this behalf;`
  line `7 [( c ) “higher education” means any course of study pursued after passing the Senior Secondary`
  line `Examination or its equivalent from any school, board or university recognised by the Central`
  line `Government or State Government or local authority or by any other authority authorised by the`
  line `Central Government or State Government or local authority to do so;]`
  line `( d ) “initial assessment year” means the assessment year relevant to the previous year, in which`
  line `the assessee starts paying the interest on the loan;]`
  line `1. Clause ( ii ) omitted by Act 20 of 2015, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 27, for “sixty - five years” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `3. Clause (5) omitted by Act 13 of 2018, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019). Earlier inserted by Act 20 of 2015, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 25, for section 80E (w.e.f. 1-4-2006). Earlier omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989)`
  line `and later inserted by Act 32 of 1994, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 27, ibid., for “notified by the Central Government” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2008).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 32, for clause ( c ) (w.e..f 1-4-2010).`
