obj_root_law_sections_347_content:
  string
  line 347
  line `1 [( e ) “relative”, in relation to an individual, means the spouse and children of that individual or`
  line `the student for whom the individual is the legal guardian.]`
  line `2 [ 80EE. Deduction in respect of interest on loan taken for residential house property. — ( 1 ) In`
  line `computing the total income of an assessee, being an individual, there shall be deducted, in accordance`
  line `with and subject to the provisions of this section, interest payable on loan taken by him from any financial`
  line `institution for the purpose of acquisition of a residential property.`
  line `( 2 ) The deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall not exceed fifty thousand rupees and shall be allowed in`
  line `computing the total income of the individual for the assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April,`
  line `2017 and subsequent assessment years.`
  line `( 3 ) The deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be subject to the following conditions, namely: —`
  line `( i ) the loan has been sanctioned by the financial institution during the period beginning on the 1st`
  line `day of April, 2016 and ending on the 31st day of March, 2017;`
  line `( ii ) the amount of loan sanctioned for acquisition of the residential house property does not`
  line `exceed thirty-five lakh rupees;`
  line `( iii ) the value of residential house property does not exceed fifty lakh rupees;`
  line `( iv ) the assessee does not own any residential house property on the date of sanction of loan.`
  line `( 4 ) Where a deduction under this section is allowed for any interest referred to in sub-section ( 1 ),`
  line `deduction shall not be allowed in respect of such interest under any other provision of this Act for the`
  line `same or any other assessment year.`
  line `( 5 ) For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “financial institution” means a banking company to which the Banking Regulation`
  line `Act, 1949 (10 of 1949) applies, or any bank or banking institution referred to in section 51 of that Act`
  line `or a housing finance company;`
  line `( b ) “housing finance company” means a public company formed or registered in India with the`
  line `main object of carrying on the business of providing long-term finance for construction or purchase`
  line `of houses in India for residential purposes.]`
  line `80F. [ Deduction in respect of educational expenses in certain cases ]. — Omitted by the Finance`
  line `Act, 1985 (32 of 1985), s. 17 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1986). Before omission by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 it was ins. by Act 4`
  line `of 1988, s. 24 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `80FF. [ Deduction in respect of expenses on higher education in certain cases ]. — Omitted by the`
  line `Finance ( No. 2) Act, 1980 (44 of 1980), s. 14 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1981). Earlier inserted by Act 25 of 1975 s. 11`
  line `( w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 32, for clause ( e ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2010). Earlier inserted by Act 22 of 2007, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 38, for section 80EE (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
