obj_root_law_sections_349_content:
  string
  line 349
  line `1 [( iiid ) the Rajiv Gandhi Foundation, the deed of declaration in respect whereof was`
  line `registered at New Delhi on the 21st day of June, 1991; or]`
  line `2 [( iiie ) the National Foundation for Communal Harmony; or]`
  line `3 [( iiif ) a University or any educational institution of national eminence as may be approved`
  line `by the prescribed authority in this behalf; or]`
  line `4 [( iiig ) the Maharashtra Chief Minister’s Relief Fund during the period beg inning on the 1st`
  line `day of October, 1993 and ending on the 6th day of October, 1993 or to the Chief Minister’s`
  line `Earthquake Relief Fund, Maharashtra; or]`
  line `5 [( iiiga ) any fund set up by the State Government of Gujarat exclusively for providing relief`
  line `to the victims of earthquake in Gujarat; or]`
  line `6 [( iiih ) any Zila Saksharta Samiti constituted in any district under the chairmanship of the`
  line `Collector of that district for the purposes of improvement of primary education in villages and`
  line `towns in such district and for literacy and postliteracy activities.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- clause, “town” means a town which has a`
  line `population not exceeding one lakh according to the last preceding census of which the relevant`
  line `figures have been published before the first day of the previous year; or]`
  line `7 [( iiiha ) the National Blood Transfusion Council or to any State Blood Transfusion Council`
  line `which has its sole object the control, supervision, regulation or encouragement in India of the`
  line `services related to operation and requirements of blood banks.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-clause, —`
  line `( a ) “National Blood Transfusion Council” means a society registered under the Societies`
  line `Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860) and has an officer not below the rank of an Additional`
  line `Secretary to the Government of India dealing with the AIDS Control Project as its Chairman,`
  line `by whatever name called;`
  line `( b ) “State Blood Transfusion Council” means a society registered, in consultation with`
  line `the National Blood Transfusion Council, under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of`
  line `1860) or under any law corresponding to that Act in force in any part of India and has`
  line `Secretary to the Government of that State dealing with the Department of Health, as its`
  line `Chairman, by whatever name called; or`
  line `( iiihb ) any fund set up by a State Government to provide medical relief to the poor; or`
  line `( iiihc ) the Army Central Welfare Fund or the Indian Naval Benevolent Fund or the Air Force`
  line `Central Welfare Fund established by the armed forces of the Union for the welfare of the past and`
  line `present members of such forces or their dependants; or]`
  line `8 [( iiihd ) the Andhra Pradesh Chief Minister’s Cyclone Relief Fund, 1996; or]`
  line `9 [( iiihe ) the National Illness Assistance Fund; or]`
  line `10 [( iiihf ) the Chief Minister’s Relief Fund or the Lieutenant Governor’s Relief Fund in respect`
  line `of any State or Union territory, as the case may be:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 38 of 1993, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `3. Ins. s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1994).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-1994).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 4 of 2001, s. 6 (w.e.f. 3-2-2001).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-1996).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-1997).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 35 of 1996, s. 2 (w.e.f. 14-11-1996).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 14 of 1997, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1997).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
