obj_root_law_sections_350_content:
  string
  line 350
  line `Provided that such Fund is —`
  line `( a ) the only Fund of its kind established in the State or the Union territory, as the case`
  line `may be;`
  line `( b ) under the overall control of the Chief Secretary or the Department of Finance of the`
  line `State or the Union territory, as the case may be;`
  line `( c ) administered in such manner as may be specified by the State Government or the`
  line `Lieutenant Governor, as the case may be; or]`
  line `1 [( iiihg ) the National Sports Fund to be set up by the Central Government; or`
  line `( iiihh ) the National Cultural Fund set up by the Central Government; or]`
  line `2 [( iiihi ) the Fund for Technology Development and Application set up by the Central`
  line `Government; or]`
  line `3 [( iiihj ) the National Trust for Welfare of Persons with Autism, Cerebral Palsy, Mental`
  line `Retardation and Multiple Disabilities constituted under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 3 of the`
  line `National Trust for Welfare of Persons with Autism, Cerebral Palsy, Mental Retardation and`
  line `Multiple Disabilities Act, 1999 (44 of 1999); or]`
  line `4 [( iiihk ) the Swachh Bharat Kosh, set up by the Central Government, other than the sum spent`
  line `by the assessee in pursuance of Corporate Social Responsibility under sub-section ( 5 ) of section`
  line `135 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013); or`
  line `( iiihl ) the Clean Ganga Fund, set up by the Central Government, where such assessee is a`
  line `resident and such sum is other than the sum spent by the assessee in pursuance of Corporate`
  line `Social Responsibility under sub-section ( 5 ) of section 135 of the Companies Act, 2013`
  line `(18 of 2013); or]`
  line `5 [( iiihm ) the National Fund for Control of Drug Abuse constituted under section 7A of the`
  line `Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Act, 1985 (61 of 1985); or]`
  line `( iv ) any other fund or any institution to which this section applies; or`
  line `( v ) the Government or any local authority, to be utilised 6 [for any charitable purpose other`
  line `than the purpose of promoting family planning; or]`
  line `7 [ 8 [( vi ) an authority constituted in India by or under any law enacted either for the purpose of`
  line `dealing with and satisfying the need for housing accommodation or for the purpose of planning,`
  line `development or improvement of cities, towns and villages, or for both;]`
  line `9 [( via ) any corporation referred to in clause ( 26BB ) of section 10; or]`
  line `( vii ) the Government or to any such local authority, institution or association as may be`
  line `approved in this behalf by the Central Government, to be utilised for the purpose of promoting`
  line `family planning;]`
  line `( b ) any sums paid by the assessee in the previous year as donations for the renovation or repair of`
  line `any such temple, mosque, gurdwara, church or other place as is notified by the Central Government`
  line `in the Official Gazette to be of historic, archaeological or artistic importance or to be a place of public`
  line `worship of renown throughout any State or States;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 29 w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 43 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 39 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 22, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 66 of 1976, s. 17, for “for any charitable purpose;” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1977).`
  line `7. Ins. by s. 17, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1977).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 30, for sub-clause ( vi ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
