obj_root_law_sections_354_content:
  string
  line 354
  line `1 [ 80GG. Deductions in respect of rents paid. — In computing the total income of an assessee, not`
  line `being an assessee having any income falling within clause ( 13A ) of section 10, there shall be deducted`
  line `any expenditure incurred by him in excess of ten per cent of his total income towards payment of rent (by`
  line `whatever name called) in respect of any furnished or unfurnished accommodation occupied by him for the`
  line `purposes of his own residence, to the extent to which such excess expenditure does not`
  line `exceed 2 [five thousand rupees ] per month or twenty-five per cent of his total income for the year,`
  line `whichever is less, and subject to such other conditions or limitations as may be prescribed, having regard`
  line `to the area or place in which such accommodation is situated and other relevant considerations:`
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to an assessee in any case where any residential`
  line `accommodation is —`
  line `( i ) owned by the assessee or by his spouse or minor child or, where such assessee is a member`
  line `of a Hindu undivided family, by such family at the place where he ordinarily resides or performs`
  line `duties of his office or employment or carries on his business or profession; or`
  line `( ii ) owned by the assessee at any other place, being accommodation in the occupation of the`
  line `assessee, the value of which is to be determined 3 [under clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 2 ) or, as the case`
  line `may be, clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 4 ) of section 23].`
  line `Explanation. —In this section, the expressions “ten per cent of his total income” and “twenty -five per`
  line `cent of his total income” shall mean ten per cent or twenty -five per cent, as the case may be, of the`
  line `assessee’s total income before allowing deduction for any expenditure under this section.]`
  line `4 [80GGA. Deduction in respect of certain donations for scientific research or rural`
  line `development. — ( 1 ) In computing the total income of an assessee, there shall be deducted, in accordance`
  line `with and subject to the provisions of this section, the sums specified in sub-section ( 2 ).`
  line `( 2 ) The sums referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be the following, namely: —`
  line `( a ) any sum paid by the assessee in the previous year to a 5 [research association] which has as its`
  line `object the undertaking of scientific research or to a University, college or other institution to be used`
  line `for scientific research:`
  line `Provided that such association, University, college or institution is for the time being approved`
  line `for the purposes of clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 35;`
  line `6 [( aa ) any sum paid by the assessee in the previous year 7 [to a research association which has as`
  line `its object the undertaking of research in social science or statistical research or to a University],`
  line `college or other institution to be used for research in social science or statistical research:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 2 016, s. 39, for “two thousand rupees” w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 40, for “under sub -clause ( i ) of clause ( a ) or, as the case may be, clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 23” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2002).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 1979, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1980). Restored to its original position by Act 3 of 1989 s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `Earlier omitted by Act 4 of 1988 s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 26, for “scientific research association” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2011).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 26, for “to a University” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2011).`
