  title `Page 357`
  content obj_root_law_sections_357_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_357_footnotes
  sourcePage 357
obj_root_law_sections_357_content:
  string
  line 357
  line `1 [Provided that no deduction shall be allowed under this section in respect of any sum contributed`
  line `by way of cash.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that for the purposes of this`
  line `section, the word “contribute”, with its grammatical variation, has the meaning assigned to it under`
  line `section 293A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).]`
  line `80GGC. Deduction in respect of contributions given by any person to political parties. — In`
  line `computing the total income of an assessee, being any person, except local authority and every artificial`
  line `juridical person wholly or partly funded by the Government, there shall be deducted any amount of`
  line `contribution made by him, in the previous year, to a political party or an electoral trust:`
  line `2 [Provided that no deduction shall be allowed under this section in respect of any sum contributed`
  line `by way of cash.]`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of sections 80GGB and 80GGC, “political party”`
  line `means a political party registered under section 29A of the Representation of the People`
  line `Act, 1951 (43 of 1951).]`
  line `C. — Deductions in respect of certain incomes`
  line `80H. [ Deduction in case of new industrial undertakings employing displaced persons,`
  line `etc.] — Omitted by the Taxation Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1975, s. 20 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `3 [80HH. Deduction in respect of profits and gains from newly established industrial`
  line `undertakings or hotel business in backward areas. — Where the gross total income of an assessee`
  line `includes any profits and gains derived from an industrial undertaking, or the business of a hotel, to which`
  line `this section applies, there shall, in accordance with and subject to the provisions of this section, be`
  line `allowed, in computing the total income of the assessee, a deduction from such profits and gains of an`
  line `amount equal to twenty per cent thereof.`
  line `( 2 ) This section applies to any industrial undertaking which fulfils all the following conditions,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( i ) it has begun or begins to manufacture or produce articles after the 31 st day of December, 1970`
  line `4 [but before the 1st day of April, 1990], in any backward area;`
  line `( ii ) it is not formed by the splitting up, or the reconstruction, of a business already in existence in`
  line `any backward area:`
  line `Provided that this condition shall not apply in respect of any industrial undertaking which is`
  line `formed as a result of the re-establishment, reconstruction or revival by the assessee of the business of`
  line `any such industrial undertaking as is referred to in section 33B, in the circumstances and within the`
  line `period specified in that section;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 18, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 26 of 1974, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
obj_root_law_sections_357_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_358:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-358
  sectionNo (358)
  orderNo 358
  title `Page 358`
  content obj_root_law_sections_358_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_358_footnotes
  sourcePage 358
obj_root_law_sections_358_content:
  string
  line 358
  line `( iii ) it is not formed by the transfer to a new business of machinery or plant previously used for`
  line `any purpose in any backward area;`
  line `( iv ) it employs ten or more workers in a manufacturing process carried on with the aid of power,`
  line `or employs twenty or more workers in a manufacturing process carried on without the aid of power.`
  line `Explanation. — Where any machinery or plant or any part thereof previously used for any purpose in`
  line `any backward area is transferred to a new business in that area or in any other backward area and the total`
  line `value of the machinery or plant or part so transferred does not exceed twenty per cent of the total value of`
  line `the machinery or plant used in the business, then, for the purposes of clause ( iii ) of this sub-section, the`
  line `condition specified therein shall be deemed to have been fulfilled.`
  line `( 3 ) This section applies to the business of any hotel, where all the following conditions are fulfilled,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( i ) the business of the hotel has started or starts functioning after the 31st day of December, 1970`
  line `1 [but before the 1st day of April, 1990], in any backward area;`
  line `( ii ) the business of the hotel is not formed by the splitting up, or the reconstruction, of a business`
  line `already in existence;`
  line `( iii ) the hotel is for the time being approved for the purposes of this sub-section by the Central`
  line Government.
  line `( 4 ) The deduction specified in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be allowed in computing the total income in`
  line `respect of each of the ten assessment years beginning with the assessment year relevant to the previous`
  line `year in which the industrial undertaking begins to manufacture or produce articles or the business of the`
  line `hotel starts functioning:`
  line `Provided that, —`
  line `( i ) in the case of an industrial undertaking which has begun to manufacture or produce articles,`
  line and
  line `( ii ) in the case of the business of a hotel which has started functioning,`
  line `after the 31st day of December, 1970, but before the 1st day of April, 1973, this sub-section shall have`
  line `effect as if the reference to ten assessment years were a reference to ten assessment years as reduced by`
  line `the number of assessment years which expired before the 1st day of April, 1974.`
  line `( 5 ) Where the assessee is a person other than a company or a co-operative society, the deduction`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) shall not be admissible unless the accounts of the industrial undertaking or the`
  line `business of the hotel for the previous year relevant to the assessment year for which the deduction is`
  line `claimed have been audited by an accountant as defined in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 288 and the assessee furnishes, along with his return of income, the report of such audit in the`
  line `prescribed form duly signed and verified by such accountant.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
obj_root_law_sections_358_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_359:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-359
  sectionNo (359)
  orderNo 359
  title `Page 359`
  content obj_root_law_sections_359_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_359_footnotes
  sourcePage 359
obj_root_law_sections_359_content:
  string
  line 359
  line `( 6 ) Where any goods held for the purposes of the business of the industrial undertaking or the hotel`
  line `are transferred to any other business carried on by the assessee, or where any goods held for the purposes`
  line `of any other business carried on by the assessee are transferred to the business of the industrial`
  line `undertaking or the hotel and, in either case, the consideration, if any, for such transfer as recorded in the`
  line `accounts of the business of the industrial undertaking or the hotel does not correspond to the market value`
  line `of such goods as on the date of the transfer, then, for the purposes of the deduction under this section, the`
  line `profits and gains of the industrial undertaking or the business of the hotel shall be computed as if the`
  line `transfer, in either case, had been made at the market value of such goods as on that date:`
  line `Provided that where, in the opinion of the 1 [Assessing Officer], the computation of the profits and`
  line `gains of the industrial undertaking or the business of the hotel in the manner hereinbefore specified`
  line `presents exceptional difficulties, the 1 [Assessing Officer] may compute such profits and gains on such`
  line `reasonable basis as he may deem fit.`
  line `Explanation. — In this sub- section, “market value” in relation to any goods means the price that such`
  line `goods would ordinarily fetch on sale in the open market.`
  line `( 7 ) Where it appears to the 1 [Assessing Officer] that, owing to the close connection between the`
  line `assessee carrying on the business of the industrial undertaking or the hotel to which this section applies`
  line `and any other person, or for any other reason, the course of business between them is so arranged that the`
  line `business transacted between them produces to the assessee more than the ordinary profits which might be`
  line `expected to arise in the business of the industrial undertaking or the hotel, the 1 [Assessing Officer] shall,`
  line `in computing the profits and gains of the industrial undertaking or the hotel for the purposes of the`
  line `deduction under this section, take the amount of profits as may be reasonably deemed to have been`
  line `derived therefrom.`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `( 9 ) In a case where the assessee is entitled also to the deduction 3 [under section 80-I or section 80J] in`
  line `relation to the profits and gains of an industrial undertaking or the business of a hotel to which this section`
  line `applies, effect shall first be given to the provisions of this section.`
  line `4 [( 9A ) Where a deduction in relation to the profits and gains of a small-scale industrial undertaking to`
  line `which section 80HHA applies is claimed and allowed under that section for any assessment year,`
  line `deduction in relation to such profits and gains shall not be allowed under this section for the same or any`
  line `other assessment year.]`
  line `( 10 ) Nothing contained in this section shall apply in relation to any undertaking engaged in mining.]`
  line `5 [( 11 ) For the purposes of this section, “backward area” means such area as t he Central Government`
  line `may, having regard to the stage of development of that area, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `specify in this behalf:`
  line `Provided that any notification under this sub-section may be issued so as to have retrospective effect`
  line `to a date not earlier than the 1st day of April, 1983.]`
  line `1. Su bs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Sub-section ( 8 ) omitted by Act 41 of 1975, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 35, for “under section 80J” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1981).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-1978).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 10, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_359_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_360:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-360
  sectionNo (360)
  orderNo 360
  title `Page 360`
  content obj_root_law_sections_360_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_360_footnotes
  sourcePage 360
obj_root_law_sections_360_content:
  string
  line 360
  line `1 [80HHA. Deduction in respect of profits and gains from newly established small-scale`
  line `industrial undertakings in certain areas. — ( 1 ) Where the gross total income of an assessee includes any`
  line `profits and gains derived from a small-scale industrial undertaking to which this section applies, there`
  line `shall, in accordance with and subject to the provisions of this section, be allowed, in computing the total`
  line `income of the assessee, a deduction from such profits and gains of an amount equal to twenty per cent`
  line thereof.
  line `( 2 ) This section applies to any small-scale industrial undertaking which fulfils all the following`
  line `conditions, namely: —`
  line `( i ) it begins to manufacture or produce articles after the 30th day of September, 1977 2 [but before`
  line `the 1st day of April, 1990], in any rural area;`
  line `( ii ) it is not formed by the splitting up, or the reconstruction, of a business already in existence:`
  line `Provided that this condition shall not apply in respect of any small-scale industrial undertaking which`
  line `is formed as a result of the re-establishment, reconstruction or revival by the assessee of the business of`
  line `any such industrial undertaking as is referred to in section 33B, in the circumstances and within the period`
  line `specified in that section;`
  line `( iii ) it is not formed by the transfer to a new business of machinery or plant previously used for`
  line `any purpose;`
  line `( iv ) it employs ten or more workers in a manufacturing process carried on with the aid of power,`
  line `or employs twenty or more workers in a manufacturing process carried on without the aid of power.`
  line `Explanation. — Where in the case of a small-scale industrial undertaking, any machinery or plant or`
  line `any part thereof previously used for any purpose is transferred to a new business and the total value of the`
  line `machinery or plant or part so transferred does not exceed twenty per cent of the total value of the`
  line `machinery or plant used in the business, then, for the purposes of clause ( iii ) of this sub-section, the`
  line `condition specified therein shall be deemed to have been fulfilled.`
  line `( 3 ) The deduction specified in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be allowed in computing the total income 3 [of`
  line `each of the ten previous years beginning with the previous year in which the industrial undertaking]`
  line `begins to manufacture or produce articles:`
  line `4 [Provided that such deduction shall not be allowed in computing the total income of any of the ten`
  line `previous years aforesaid in respect of which the industrial undertaking is not a small-scale industrial`
  line `undertaking within the meaning of clause ( b ) of the Explanation below sub-section ( 8 ).]`
  line `( 4 ) Where the assessee is a person, other than a company or a co-operative society, the deduction`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) shall not be admissible unless the accounts of the small-scale industrial undertaking`
  line `for the previous year relevant to the assessment year for which the deduction is claimed have been audited`
  line `by an accountant as defined in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288 and the assessee`
  line `furnishes, along with his return of income, the report of such audit in the prescribed form duly signed and`
  line `verified by such accountant.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-1978).`
  line `2. Ins. by 12 of 1990, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 16 of 1981, s. 10, for “in respect of each of th e ten assessment years beginning with the assessment year`
  line `relevant to the previous year in which the small- scale industrial undertaking” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1981).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1981).`
obj_root_law_sections_360_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_361:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-361
  sectionNo (361)
  orderNo 361
  title `Page 361`
  content obj_root_law_sections_361_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_361_footnotes
  sourcePage 361
obj_root_law_sections_361_content:
  string
  line 361
  line `( 5 ) The provisions of sub-sections ( 6 ) and ( 7 ) of section 80HH shall, so far as may be, apply in`
  line `relation to the computation of the profits and gains of a small-scale industrial undertaking for the`
  line `purposes of the deduction under this section as they apply in relation to the computation of the profits and`
  line `gains of an industrial undertaking for the purposes of the deduction under that section.`
  line `( 6 ) In a case where the assessee is entitled also to the deduction 1 [under section 80-I or section 80J] in`
  line `relation to the profits and gains of a small-scale industrial undertaking to which this section applies, effect`
  line `shall first be given to the provisions of this section.`
  line `( 7 ) Where a deduction in relation to the profits and gains of a small-scale industrial undertaking to`
  line `which section 80HH applies is claimed and allowed under that section for any assessment year, deduction`
  line `in relation to such profits and gains shall not be allowed under this section for the same or any other`
  line `assessment year.`
  line `( 8 ) Nothing contained in this section shall apply in relation to any small-scale industrial undertaking`
  line `engaged in mining.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `2 [( a ) “rural area” means any area other than—`
  line `( i ) an area which is comprised within the jurisdiction of a municipality (whether known as a`
  line `municipality, municipal corporation, notified area committee, town area committee, town`
  line `committee or by any other name) or a cantonment board and which has a population of not less`
  line `than ten thousand according to the last preceding census of which the relevant figures have been`
  line `published before the first day of the previous year; or`
  line `( ii ) an area within such distance, not being more than fifteen kilometres from the local limits`
  line `of any municipality or cantonment board referred to in sub-clause ( i ), as the Central Government`
  line `may, having regard to the stage of development of such area (including the extent of, and scope`
  line `for, urbanisation of such area) and other relevant considerations specify in this behalf by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette;]`
  line `3 [( b ) an industrial undertaking shall be deemed to be a small-scale industrial undertaking which`
  line `is, on the last day of the previous year, regarded as a small-scale industrial undertaking under section`
  line `11B of the Industries (Development and Regulation) Act, 1951 (65 of 1951).]`
  line `4 [80HHB. Deduction in respect of profits and gains from projects outside India. — ( 1 ) Where the`
  line `gross total income of an assessee being an Indian company or a person (other than a company) who is`
  line `resident in India includes any profits and gains derived from the business of —`
  line `( a ) the execution of a foreign project undertaken by the assessee in pursuance of a contract`
  line `entered into by him, or`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 35, for “under section 80J” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1981).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 126, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 44, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1978).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 14 of 1982, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_361_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_362:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-362
  sectionNo (362)
  orderNo 362
  title `Page 362`
  content obj_root_law_sections_362_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_362_footnotes
  sourcePage 362
obj_root_law_sections_362_content:
  string
  line 362
  line `( b ) the execution of any work undertaken by him and forming part of a foreign project`
  line `undertaken by any other person in pursuance of a contract entered into by such other person,`
  line `with the Government of a foreign State or any statutory or other public authority or agency in a foreign`
  line `State, or a foreign enterprise, there shall, in accordance with and subject to the provisions of this section,`
  line `be allowed, in computing the total income of the assessee, 1 [a deduction from such profits and gains of an`
  line `amount equal to —`
  line `( i ) forty per cent. thereof for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2001;`
  line `( ii ) thirty per cent. thereof for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2002;`
  line `( iii ) twenty per cent. thereof for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2003;`
  line `( iv ) ten per cent. thereof for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2004,`
  line `and no deduction shall be allowed in respect of the assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April,`
  line `2005 and any subsequent assessment year:]`
  line `Provided that the consideration for the execution of such project or, as the case may be, of such work`
  line `is payable in convertible foreign exchange.`
  line `( 2 ) For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “convertible foreign exchange” means foreign exchange which is fo r the time being treated`
  line `by the Reserve Bank of India as convertible foreign exchange for the purposes of 2 [the Foreign`
  line `Exchange Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999)], and any rules made thereunder;`
  line `( b ) “foreign project” means a project for—`
  line `( i ) the construction of any building, road, dam, bridge or other structure outside India;`
  line `( ii ) the assembly or installation of any machinery or plant outside India;`
  line `( iii ) the execution of such other work (of whatever nature) as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 3 ) The deduction under this section shall be allowed only if the following conditions are fulfilled,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( i ) the assessee maintains separate accounts in respect of the profits and gains derived from the`
  line `business of the execution of the foreign project, or, as the case may be, of the work forming part of`
  line `the foreign project undertaken by him and, where the assessee is a person other than an Indian`
  line `company or a co-operative society, such accounts have been audited by an accountant as defined in`
  line `the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288 and the assessee furnishes, along with his return`
  line `of income, the report of such audit in the prescribed form duly signed and verified by such`
  line accountant;
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 32, for “a deduction from such profits and gains of an amount equal to fifty per cent. thereof”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 4, for “the Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_362_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_363:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-363
  sectionNo (363)
  orderNo 363
  title `Page 363`
  content obj_root_law_sections_363_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_363_footnotes
  sourcePage 363
obj_root_law_sections_363_content:
  string
  line 363
  line `1 [( ia ) the assessee furnishes, along with his return of income, a certificate in the prescribed`
  line `form from an accountant as defined in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288, duly`
  line `signed and verified by such accountant, certifying that the deduction has been correctly claimed in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this section;]`
  line `( ii ) an amount equal to 2 [such percentage of the profits and gains as is referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) in relation to the relevant assessment year] is debited to the profit and loss account of`
  line `the previous year in respect of which the deduction under this section is to be allowed and credited to`
  line `a reserve account (to be called the “Foreign Projects Reserve Account”) to be utilised by the assessee`
  line `during a period of five years next following for the purposes of his business other than for distribution`
  line `by way of dividends or profits;`
  line `( iii ) an amount equal to 2 [such percentage of the profits and gains as is referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) in relation to the relevant assessment year] is brought by the assessee in convertible`
  line `foreign exchange into India, in accordance with the provisions of the Foreign Exchange Management`
  line `Act, 1999 (42 of 1999), and any rules made thereunder, within a period of six months from the end of`
  line `the previous year referred to in clause ( ii ) or, 3 [within such further period as the competent authority`
  line `may allow in this behalf:]`
  line `Provided that where the amount credited by the assessee to the Foreign Projects Reserve Account`
  line `in pursuance of clause ( ii ) or the amount brought into India by the assessee in pursuance of clause ( iii )`
  line `or each of the said amounts is less than 2 [such percentage of the profits and gains as is referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) in relation to the relevant assessment year], the deduction under that sub-section shall`
  line `be limited to the amount so credited in pursuance of clause ( ii ) or the amount so brought into India in`
  line `pursuance of clause ( iii ), whichever is less.`
  line `1 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of clause ( iii ), the expression “competent authority” means the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India or such other authority as is authorised under any law for the time being in force`
  line `for regulating payments and dealings in foreign exchange.]`
  line `( 4 ) If at any time before the expiry of five years from the end of the previous year in which the`
  line `deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) is allowed, the assesseeutilises the amount credited to the Foreign`
  line `Projects Reserve Account for distribution by way of dividends or profits or for any other purpose which is`
  line `not a purpose of the business of the assessee, the deduction originally allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) shall`
  line `be deemed to have been wrongly allowed, and the 4 [Assessing Officer] may, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act, recompute the total income of the assessee for the relevant previous year and make`
  line `the necessary amendment; and the provisions of section 154 shall, so far as may be, apply thereto, the`
  line `period of four years specified in sub-section ( 7 ) of that section being reckoned from the end of the`
  line `previous year in which the money was so utilised.`
  line `( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Chapter under the heading ”`
  line `C. —Deductions in respect of certain incomes”, no part of the consideration or of the income comprised in`
  line `the consideration payable to the assessee for the execution of a foreign project referred to in clause ( a ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) or of any work referred to in clause ( b ) of that sub-section shall qualify for deduction for`
  line `any assessment year under any such other provision.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 33, for “fifty per cent. of the profits and gains referred to in sub -section ( 1 )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2001).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 45, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
