  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_364_footnotes
  sourcePage 364
obj_root_law_sections_364_content:
  string
  line 364
  line `1 [80HHBA. Deduction in respect of profits and gains from housing projects in certain`
  line `cases. — ( 1 ) Where the gross total income of an assessee being an Indian company or a person (other than`
  line `a company) who is a resident in India includes any profits and gains derived from the execution of a`
  line `housing project awarded to the assessee on the basis of global tender and such project is aided by the`
  line `World Bank, there shall, in accordance with and subject to the provisions of this section, be allowed, in`
  line `computing the total income of the assessee, 2 [a deduction from such profits and gains of an amount equal`
  line `to ––`
  line `( i ) forty per cent. thereof for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2001;`
  line `( ii ) thirty per cent. thereof for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2002;`
  line `( iii ) twenty per cent. thereof for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2003;`
  line `( iv ) ten per cent. thereof for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2004,`
  line `and no deduction shall be allowed in respect of the assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April,`
  line `2005 and any subsequent assessment year.]`
  line `( 2 ) The deductions under this section shall be allowed only if the following conditions are fulfilled,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( i ) the assessee maintains separate accounts in respect of the profits and gains derived from the`
  line `business of the execution of the housing project undertaken by him and, where the assessee is a`
  line `person other than an Indian company or a co-operative society, such accounts have been audited by`
  line `an accountant as defined in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288 and the assessee`
  line `furnishes along with his return of income the report of such audit in the prescribed form duly signed`
  line `and verified by such accountant;`
  line `( ii ) an amount equal to 3 [such percentage of the profits and gains as is referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) in relation to the relevant assessment year] is debited to the profit and loss account of`
  line `the previous year in respect of which the deduction under this section is to be allowed and credited to`
  line `a reserve account (to be called the Housing Projects Reserve Account) to be utilised by the assessee`
  line `during a period of five years next following for the purposes of his business other than for distribution`
  line `by way of dividends or profit:`
  line `Provided that where the amount credited by the assessee to the Housing Projects Reserve Account in`
  line `pursuance of clause ( ii ) is less than 3 [such percentage of the profits and gains as is referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) in relation to the relevant assessment year], the deduction under this section shall be`
  line `limited to the amount so credited in pursuance of clause ( ii ).`
  line `( 3 ) If at any time before the expiry of five years from the end of the previous year in which the`
  line `deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) is allowed, the assesseeutilises the amount credited to the Housing`
  line `Projects Reserve Account for distribution by way of dividends or profit or for any other purpose which is`
  line `not a purpose of the business of the assessee, the deduction originally allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) shall`
  line `be deemed to have been wrongly allowed and the Assessing Officer may, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act, recompute the total income of the assessee for the relevant previous year and make`
  line `necessary amendment and the provision of section 154 shall, so far as may be, apply thereto, the period of`
  line `four years specified in sub-section ( 7 ) of that section being reckoned from the end of the previous year in`
  line `which the money was so utilised.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 33, for “a deduction from such profits and gains of an amount equal to fifty per cent.thereof”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 33, for “fifty per cent. of the profits and gains referred to in sub -section ( 1 )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2001).`
