obj_root_law_sections_365_content:
  string
  line 365
  line `( 4 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Chapter under heading “ C. —`
  line `Deduction in respect of certain incomes ”, no part of the income payable to the assessee for the execution`
  line `of a housing project under sub-section ( 1 ) shall qualify for deduction for any assessment year under any`
  line `other provision.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “housing project” means a project for—`
  line `( i ) the construction of any building, road, bridge or other structure in any part of India;`
  line `( ii ) the execution of such other work (of whatever nature) as may be prescribed;`
  line `( b ) “World Bank” means the International Bank for Reconstruction and Development Bank`
  line `referred to in the International Monetary Fund and Bank Act, 1945.]`
  line `1 [80HHC.Deduction in respect of profits retained for export business. — 2 [( 1 ) Where an assessee,`
  line `being an Indian company or a person (other than a company) resident in India, is engaged in the business`
  line `of export out of India of any goods or merchandise to which this section applies, there shall, in`
  line `accordance with and subject to the provisions of this section, be allowed, in computing the total income of`
  line `the assessee, 3 [a deduction to the extent of profits, referred to in sub-section ( 1B )], derived by the assessee`
  line `from the export of such goods or merchandise:`
  line `Provided that if the assessee, being a holder of an Export House Certificate or a Trading House`
  line `Certificate (hereafter in this section referred to as an Export House or a Trading House, as the case may`
  line `be,) issues a certificate referred to in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 4A ), that in respect of the amount of the`
  line `export turnover specified therein, the deduction under this sub-section is to be allowed to a supporting`
  line `manufacturer, then the amount of deduction in the case of the assessee shall be reduced by such amount`
  line `which bears to the 4 [total profits derived by the assessee from the export of trading goods, the same`
  line `proportion as the amount of export turnover specified in the said certificate bears to the total export`
  line `turnover of the assessee in respect of such trading goods].`
  line `( 1A ) Where the assessee, being a supporting manufacturer, has during the previous year, sold goods`
  line `or merchandise to any Export House or Trading House in respect of which the Export House or Trading`
  line `House has issued a certificate under the proviso to sub-section ( 1 ), there shall, in accordance with and`
  line `subject to the provisions of this section, be allowed in computing the total income of the assessee, 3 [a`
  line `deduction to the extent of profits, referred to in sub-section ( 1B )], derived by the assessee from the sale of`
  line `goods or merchandise to the Export House or Trading House in respect of which the certificate has been`
  line `issued by the Export House or Trading House.]`
  line `5 [( 1B ) For the purposes of sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 1A ), the extent of deduction of the profits shall be an`
  line `amount equal to —`
  line `( i ) eighty per cent. thereof for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2001;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 1985, s. 19, for section HHC (w.e.f. 1-4-1986).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 24, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 34, for “a deduction of the profits” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2001).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s.46, for “total profits of the export business of the assessee the same proportion as the amount`
  line `of export turnover specified in the said certificate bears to the total export turnover of the assessee" (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
