obj_root_law_sections_366_content:
  string
  line 366
  line `1 [( ii ) seventy per cent. thereof for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2002;`
  line `( iii ) fifty per cent. thereof for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2003;`
  line `( iv ) thirty per cent. thereof for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2004,]`
  line `and no deduction shall be allowed in respect of the assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April,`
  line `2005 and any subsequent assessment year.]`
  line `( 2 ) ( a ) This section applies to all goods or merchandise, other than those specified in clause ( b ), if the`
  line `sale proceeds of such goods or merchandise exported out of India are 2 [received in, or brought into, India]`
  line `by the assessee 3 [(other than the supporting manufacturer)] in convertible foreign exchange 4 [, within a`
  line `period of six months from the end of the previous year or, 5 [within such further period as the competent`
  line `authority may allow in this behalf].]`
  line `6 [ Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, the expression “competent authority” means the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India or such other authority as is authorised under any law for the time being in force`
  line `for regulating payments and dealings in foreign exchange.]`
  line `( b ) This section does not apply to the following goods or merchandise, namely: —`
  line `( i ) mineral oil; and`
  line `( ii ) minerals and ores 7 [(other than processed minerals and ores specified in the Twelfth`
  line `Schedule)].`
  line `8 [ Explanation 1. — The sale proceeds referred to in clause ( a ) shall be deemed to have been received`
  line `in India where such sale proceeds are credited to a separate account maintained for the purpose by the`
  line `assessee with any bank outside India with the approval of the Reserve Bank of India.`
  line `Explanation 2. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that where any goods or`
  line `merchandise are transferred by an assessee to a branch, office, warehouse or any other establishment of`
  line `the assessee situate outside India and such goods or merchandise are sold from such branch, office,`
  line `warehouse or establishment, then, such transfer shall be deemed to be export out of India of such goods`
  line `and merchandise and the value of such goods or merchandise declared in the shipping bill or bill of export`
  line `as referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 50 of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962), shall, for the`
  line `purposes of this section, be deemed to be the sale proceeds thereof.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 41, for sub-clauses ( ii ), ( iii ) and ( iv )(w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 22, for “receivable” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1991).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 22, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 22, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 46, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `6. Ins. by s. 46, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `8. Ins. by s. 28, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
