obj_root_law_sections_367_content:
  string
  line 367
  line `1 [( 3 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), —`
  line `( a ) where the export out of India is of goods or merchandise 2 [manufactured or processed by the`
  line `assessee], the profits derived from such export shall be the amount which bears to the profits of the`
  line `business, the same proportion as the export turnover in respect of such goods bears to the total`
  line `turnover of the business carried on by the assessee;`
  line `( b ) where the export out of India is of trading goods, the profits derived from such export shall be`
  line `the export turnover in respect of such trading goods as reduced by the direct costs and indirect costs`
  line `attributable to such export;`
  line `( c ) where the export out of India is of goods or merchandise 2 [manufactured or processed by the`
  line `assessee] and of trading goods, the profits derived from such export shall, —`
  line `( i ) in respect of the goods or merchandise 2 [manufactured or processed by the assessee], be`
  line `the amount which bears to the adjusted profits of the business, the same proportion as the`
  line `adjusted export turnover in respect of such goods bears to the adjusted total turnover of the`
  line `business carried on by the assessee; and`
  line `( ii ) in respect of trading goods, be the export turnover in respect of such trading goods as`
  line `reduced by the direct and indirect costs attributable to export of such trading goods:`
  line `Provided that the profits computed under clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ) of this sub-section shall`
  line `be further increased by the amount which bears to ninety per cent of any sum referred to in clause ( iiia )`
  line `(not being profits on sale of a licence acquired from any other person), and clauses ( iiib ) and ( iiic )`
  line `of section 28, the same proportion as the export turnover bears to the total turnover of the business carried`
  line `on by the assessee:`
  line `3 [Provided further that in the case of an assessee having export turnover not exceeding rupees ten`
  line `crores during the previous year, the profits computed under clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ) of this`
  line `sub-section or after giving effect to the first proviso, as the case may be, shall be further increased by the`
  line `amount which bears to ninety per cent of any sum referred to in clause ( iiid ) or clause ( iiie ), as the case`
  line `may be, of section 28, the same proportion as the export turnover bears to the total turnover of the`
  line `business carried on by the assessee:`
  line `Provided also that in the case of an assessee having export turnover exceeding rupees ten crores`
  line `during the previous year, the profits computed under clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ) of this sub-`
  line `section or after giving effect to the first proviso, as the case may be, shall be further increased by the`
  line `amount which bears to ninety per cent. of any sum referred to in clause ( iiid ) of section 28, the same`
  line `proportion as the export turnover bears to the total turnover of the business carried on by the assessee, if`
  line `the assessee has necessary and sufficient evidence to prove that, —`
  line `( a ) he had an option to choose either the duty drawback or the Duty Entitlement Pass Book`
  line `Scheme, being the Duty Remission Scheme; and`
  line `( b ) the rate of drawback credit attributable to the customs duty was higher than the rate of credit`
  line `allowable under the Duty Entitlement Pass Book Scheme, being the Duty Remission Scheme:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 28, for sub-section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s.46, for “manufactured by the assessee” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1992).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 55 of 2005, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
obj_root_law_sections_367_footnotes:
