  line
obj_root_law_sections_368:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-368
  sectionNo (368)
  orderNo 368
  title `Page 368`
  content obj_root_law_sections_368_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_368_footnotes
  sourcePage 368
obj_root_law_sections_368_content:
  string
  line 368
  line `Provided also that in the case of an assessee having export turnover exceeding rupees ten crores`
  line `during the previous year, the profits computed under clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ) of this sub-`
  line `section or after giving effect to the first proviso, as the case may be, shall be further increased by the`
  line `amount which bears to ninety per cent of any sum referred to in clause ( iiie ) of section 28, the same`
  line `proportion as the export turnover bears to the total turnover of the business carried on by the assessee, if`
  line `the assessee has necessary and sufficient evidence to prove that, —`
  line `( a ) he had an option to choose either the duty drawback or the Duty Free Replenishment`
  line `Certificate, being the Duty Remission Scheme; and`
  line `( b ) the rate of drawback credit attributable to the customs duty was higher than the rate of credit`
  line `allowable under the Duty Free Replenishment Certificate, being the Duty Remission Scheme.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, “rate of credit allowable” means the rate of credit`
  line `allowable under the Duty Free Replenishment Certificate, being the Duty Remission Scheme calculated`
  line `in the manner as may be notified by the Central Government:]`
  line `1 [Provided also that in case the computation under clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ) of this`
  line `sub-section is a loss, such loss shall be set off against the amount which bears to ninety per cent of —`
  line `( a ) any sum referred to in clause ( iiia ) or clause ( iiib ) or clause ( iiic ), as the case may be, or`
  line `( b ) any sum referred to in clause ( iiid ) or clause ( iiie ), as the case may be, of section 28, as`
  line `applicable in the case of an assessee referred to in the second or the third or the fourth proviso, as the`
  line `case may be,`
  line `the same proportion as the export turnover bears to the total turnover of the business carried on by the`
  line assessee.]
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, —`
  line `( a ) “adjusted export turnover” means the export turnover as reduced by the export turnover in`
  line `respect of trading goods;`
  line `( b ) “adjusted profits of the business” means the profits of the business as reduced by the profits`
  line `derived from the business of export out of India of trading goods as computed in the manner provided`
  line `in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 3 );`
  line `( c ) “adjusted total turnover” means the total turnover of the business as reduced by the export`
  line `turnover in respect of trading goods;`
  line `( d ) “direct costs” means costs directly attributable to the trading goods exported out of India`
  line `including the purchase price of such goods;`
  line `( e ) “indirect costs” means costs, not being direct costs, allocated in the ratio of the export`
  line `turnover in respect of trading goods to the total turnover;`
  line `( f ) “trading goods” means goods which are not 2 [manufactured or processed by the assessee].`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 55 of 2005, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s.46, for “manufactured by the assessee” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1992).`
