obj_root_law_sections_369_content:
  string
  line 369
  line `1 [( 3A ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1A ), profits derived by a supporting manufacturer from the`
  line `sale of goods or merchandise shall be, —`
  line `( a ) in a case where the business carried on by the supporting manufacturer consists exclusively`
  line `of sale of goods or merchandise to one or more Export Houses or Trading Houses, the profits of the`
  line `business 2 ***;`
  line `( b ) in a case where the business carried on by the supporting manufacturer does not consist`
  line `exclusively of sale of goods or merchandise to one or more Export Houses or Trading Houses, the`
  line `amount which bears to the profits of the business 2 *** the same proportion as the turnover in respect`
  line `of sale to the respective Export House or Trading House bears to the total turnover of the business`
  line `carried on by the assessee.]`
  line `3 [( 4 ) The deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall not be admissible unless the assessee furnishes in the`
  line `prescribed form, along with the return of income, the report of an accountant, as defined in`
  line `the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288, certifying that the deduction has been correctly`
  line `claimed 4 [in accordance with the provisions of this section:]]`
  line `5 [Provided that in the case of an undertaking referred to in sub-section ( 4C ), the assessee shall also`
  line `furnish along with the return of income, a certificate from the undertaking in the special economic zone`
  line `containing such particulars as may be prescribed, duly certified by the auditor auditing the accounts of the`
  line `undertaking in the special economic zone under the provisions of this Act or under any other law for the`
  line `time being in force.]`
  line `1 [( 4A ) The deduction under sub-section ( 1A ) shall not be admissible unless the supporting`
  line `manufacturer furnishes in the prescribed form along with his return of income, —`
  line `( a ) the report of an accountant, as defined in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 288, certifying that the deduction has been correctly claimed on the basis of the 6 [profits] of`
  line `the supporting manufacturer in respect of his sale of goods or merchandise to the Export House or`
  line `Trading House; and`
  line `( b ) a certificate from the Export House or Trading House containing such particulars as may be`
  line `prescribed and verified in the manner prescribed that in respect of the export turnover mentioned in`
  line `the certificate, the Export House or Trading House has not claimed the deduction under this section:`
  line `Provided that the certificate specified in clause ( b ) shall be duly certified by the auditor auditing`
  line `the accounts of the Export House or Trading House under the provisions of this Act or under any`
  line `other law.]`
  line `7 [( 4B ) For the purposes of computing the total income under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 1A ), any`
  line `income not charged to tax under this Act shall be excluded.]`
  line `5 [( 4C ) The provisions of this section shall apply to an assessee, —`
  line `( a ) for an assessment year beginning after the 31st day of March, 2004 and ending before the 1st`
  line `day of April, 2005;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. The words “as computed under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession” omitted by Act 49 of 1991, s. 28`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 28, for “on the basic of the amount of export turnover” (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).earlier the words`
  line `“export turnover” were substituted for certain words by Act 46 of 1986, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 37 (w.e.f 1-4-2004).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier subs-section ( 4A ) inserted by 26 of 1988, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999,s. 46 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
