obj_root_law_sections_371_content:
  string
  line 371
  line `1 [ 80HHD. Deduction in respect of earnings in convertible foreign exchange. — ( 1 ) Where an`
  line `assessee, being an Indian company or a person (other than a company) resident in India, is engaged in the`
  line `business of a hotel or of a tour operator, approved by the prescribed authorityin this behalf or of a travel`
  line `agent, there shall, in accordance with and subject to the provisions of this section, be allowed, 2 [in`
  line `computing the total income of the assessee —`
  line `( a ) for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2001, a deduction of a sum equal to`
  line `the aggregate of —`
  line `( i ) forty per cent. of the profits derived by him from services provided to foreign tourists; and`
  line `( ii ) so much of the amount not exceeding forty per cent of the profits referred to in`
  line `sub-clause ( i ) as is debited to the profit and loss account of the previous year in respect of which`
  line `the deduction is to be allowed and credited to a reserve account to be utilised for the purposes of`
  line `the business of the assessee in the manner laid down in sub-section ( 4 );`
  line `( b ) for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2002, a deduction of a sum equal to`
  line `the aggregate of —`
  line `( i ) thirty per cent of the profits derived by him from services provided to foreign tourists; and`
  line `( ii ) so much of the amount not exceeding thirty per cent of the profits referred to in sub-`
  line `clause ( i ) as is debited to the profit and loss account of the previous year in respect of which the`
  line `deduction is to be allowed and credited to a reserve account to be utilised for the purposes of the`
  line `business of the assessee in the manner laid down in sub-section ( 4 );`
  line `( c ) for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2003, a deduction of a sum equal to`
  line `the aggregate of —`
  line `( i ) 3 [twenty-five per cent.] of the profits derived by him from services provided to foreign`
  line `tourists; and`
  line `( ii ) so much of the amount not exceeding 3 [twenty-five per cent.] of the profits referred to in`
  line `sub-clause ( i ) as is debited to the profit and loss account of the previous year in respect of which`
  line `the deduction is to be allowed and credited to a reserve account to be utilised for the purposes of`
  line `the business of the assessee in the manner laid down in sub-section ( 4 );`
  line `( d ) for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2004, a deduction of a sum equal to`
  line `the aggregate of —`
  line `( i ) 4 [fifteen per cent.] of the profits derived by him from services provided to foreign tourists;`
  line and
  line `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 35, for certain words, brackets, letters and figures (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 32, for “twenty per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2003).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 32, ibid., for “ten per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2003).`
