obj_root_law_sections_372_content:
  string
  line 372
  line `( ii ) so much of the amount not exceeding 1 [fifteen per cent.] of the profits referred to in`
  line `sub-clause ( i ) as is debited to the profit and loss account of the previous year in respect of which`
  line `the deduction is to be allowed and credited to a reserve account to be utilised for the purposes of`
  line `the business of the assessee in the manner laid down in sub-section ( 4 ),`
  line `and no deduction shall be allowed in respect of the assessment year beginning on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2005 and any subsequent assessment year]:`
  line `2 [Provided that a hotel or, as the case may be, a tour operator approved by the prescribed authority on`
  line `or after the 30th day of November, 1989 and before the 1st day of October, 1991, shall be deemed to have`
  line `been approved by the prescribed authority for the purposes of this section in relation to the assessment`
  line `year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1989 or the 1st day of April, 1990 or, as the case may be, the`
  line `1st day of April, 1991 if the assessee was engaged in the business of such hotel or as such tour operator`
  line `during the previous year relevant to any of the said assessment years.]`
  line `( 2 ) This section applies only to services provided to foreign tourists the receipts in relation to which`
  line `are received 3 [in, or brought into, India by the assessee in convertible foreign exchange within a period of`
  line `six months from the end of the previous year or, 4 [within such further period as the competent authority`
  line `may allow in this behalf]].`
  line `5 [ Explanation 6 [ 1 ]. — For the purposes of this sub-section, any payment received by an assessee,`
  line `engaged in the business of a hotel or of a tour operator or of a travel agent, in Indian currency obtained by`
  line `conversion of foreign exchange brought into India through an authorised dealer, 7 [from another hotelier,`
  line `tour operator or travel agent, as the case may be,] on behalf of a foreign tourist or group of foreign`
  line `tourists, shall be deemed to have been received by the assessee in convertible foreign exchange if the`
  line `person making the payment furnishes to the assessee a certificate specified in sub-section ( 2A ).]`
  line `8 [ Explanation 2. — For the purposes of this sub-section, the express ion “competent authority” means`
  line `the Reserve Bank of India or such other authority as is authorised under any law for the time being in`
  line `force for regulating payments and dealings in foreign exchange.]`
  line `9 [( 2A ) Every person making payment to an assessee referred to in the 10 [ Explanation 1] to sub-section`
  line `( 2 ) out of Indian currency obtained by conversion of foreign exchange received from or on behalf of a`
  line `foreign tourist or a group of foreign tourists shall furnish to that assessee a certificate in the prescribed`
  line `form indicating the amount received in foreign exchange, its conversion into Indian currency and such`
  line `other particulars as may be prescribed.]`
  line `11 [( 3 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), profits derived from services provided to foreign tourists`
  line `shall be t he amount which bears to the profits of the business (as computed under the head “Profits and`
  line `gains of business or profession”) the same proportion as the receipts specified in sub -section ( 2 ) 12 [as`
  line `reduced by any payment, referred to in sub-section ( 2A ), made by the assessee] bear to the total receipts`
  line `of the business carried on by the assessee.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 32, for “ten per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2003).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 23, for “by the assessee in convertible foreign exchange” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1991).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 47, for certain words and brackets (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `6. Explanation renumbered as Explanation 1 thereof by Act 27 of 1999, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 25, for “from a tour operator or, as the case may be, a travel agent” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1995).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 47, for “ Explanation ” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1999).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 23, for sub-section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `12. Ins. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
