obj_root_law_sections_374_content:
  string
  line 374
  line `Explanation. — A person shall be treated as having acquired any shares on the date on which his name`
  line `is entered in relation to those shares in the register of members of the public company.]`
  line `( 6 ) The deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall not be admissible unless the assessee furnishes in the`
  line `prescribed form, along with the return of income, the report of an accountant, as defined in`
  line `the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288, certifying that the deduction has been correctly`
  line `claimed on the basis of the 1 [ 2 *** amount of convertible foreign exchange received by the assessee for`
  line `services provided by him to foreign tourists 3 [, payments made by him to any assessee referred to in sub-`
  line `section ( 2A )] and the payments received by him in Indian currency as referred to in the 4 [ Explanation 1 to`
  line `sub-section ( 2 )].]`
  line `5 [( 7 ) Where a deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) is claimed and allowed in respect of profits derived`
  line `from the business of a hotel, such part of profits shall not qualify to that extent for deduction for any`
  line `assessment year under any other provisions of this Chapter under the heading “ C. — Deductions in respect`
  line `of certain incomes ”, and shall in no case exceed the profits and gains of such hotel.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “travel agent” means a travel agent or other person (not being an airline or a shipping`
  line `company) who holds a valid licence granted by the Reserve Bank of India under section 32 of 6 [the`
  line `Foreign Exchange Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999)];`
  line `( b ) “convertible foreign exchange” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( a ) of`
  line `the Explanation to section 80HHC;`
  line `( c ) “services provided to foreign tourists” shall not include services by way of sale in any shop`
  line `owned or managed by the person who carries on the business of a hotel or of a tour operator or of a`
  line `travel agent;`
  line `7 [ d ) “authorised dealer”, “foreign exchange” and “Indian currency” shall have the meanings`
  line `respectively assigned to them in clauses ( b ), ( h ) and ( k ) of section 2 of the 7 [Foreign Exchange`
  line `Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999)];]`
  line `8 [( e ) “eligible issue of capital” means an issue made by a public company formed and registered`
  line `in India and the entire proceeds of the issue is utilised wholly and exclusively for the purpose of`
  line `carrying on the business of —`
  line `( i ) setting up and running of new hotels approved by the prescribed authority; or`
  line `( ii ) providing such new facility for the growth of tourism in India, as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 29, for “amount of convertible foreign exchange received by the assessee for services`
  line `provided by him to the foreign tourist” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1992).`
  line `2. The words “aggregate of the” omitted by Act 32 of 1994, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 47, for “ Explanation to sub-section ( 2 )” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1999).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 4, for “the Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1973” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
