obj_root_law_sections_375_content:
  string
  line 375
  line `1 [80HHE.Deduction in respect of profits form export of computer software, etc. — ( 1 ) Where an`
  line `assessee, being an Indian company or a person (other than a company) resident in India, is engaged in the`
  line `business of, —`
  line `( i ) export out of India of computer software or its transmission from India to a place outside India`
  line `by any means;`
  line `( ii ) providing technical services outside India in connection with the development or production`
  line `of computer software,`
  line `there shall, in accordance with and subject to the provisions of this section, be allowed, in computing the`
  line `total income of the assessee, 2 [a deduction to the extent of the profits, referred to in sub-section ( 1B ),]`
  line `derived by the assessee from such business:`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 [Provided that if the assessee, being a company, engaged in the export out of India of computer`
  line `software, issues a certificate referred to in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 4A ), that in respect of the amount of`
  line `the export specified therein, the deduction under this sub-section is to be allowed to a supporting software`
  line `developer, then the amount of deduction in the case of an assessee shall be reduced by such amount which`
  line `bears to the total profits derived by the assessee from the export, the same proportion as the amount of the`
  line `export turnover specified in such certificate bears to the total export turnover of the assessee.`
  line `5 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the profits and gains derived`
  line `from on site development of computer software (including services for development of software) outside`
  line `India shall be deemed to be the profits and gains derived from the export of computer software outside`
  line India.]
  line `( 1A ) Where the assessee, being a supporting software developer, has during the previous year,`
  line `developed and sold computer software to an exporting company in respect of which the said company has`
  line `issued a certificate under the proviso to sub-section ( 1 ), there shall, in accordance with and subject to the`
  line `provisions of this section, be allowed in computing the total income of the assessee a deduction of the`
  line `profits derived by the assessee from the developing and selling of computer software to the exporting`
  line `company in respect of which the certificate has been issued by the said company 6 [to such extent and for`
  line `such years as specified in sub-section ( 1B )].]`
  line `6 [( 1B ) For the purposes of sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 1A ), the extent of deduction of profits shall be an`
  line `amount equal to —`
  line `( i ) eighty per cent. of such profits for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2001;`
  line `7 [( ii ) seventy per cent. thereof for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2002;`
  line `( iii ) fifty per cent. thereof for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2003;`
  line `( iv ) thirty per cent. thereof for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2004,]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 36, for “a deduction of the profits” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2001).`
  line `3. The proviso omitted by 22 of 1995, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-1996).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s.33 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 42, for sub-clauses ( ii ), ( iii ) and ( iv ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
