obj_root_law_sections_376_content:
  string
  line 376
  line `and no deduction shall be allowed in respect of the assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April,`
  line `2005 and any subsequent assessment year.]`
  line `( 2 ) The deduction specified in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be allowed only if the consideration in respect of`
  line `the computer software referred to in that sub-section is received in, or brought into, India by the assessee`
  line `in convertible foreign exchange, within a period of six months from the end of the previous year or,`
  line `1 [within such further period as the competent authority may allow in this behalf.]`
  line `Explanation 2 [1]. — The said consideration shall be deemed to have been received in India where it is`
  line `credited to a separate account maintained for the purpose by the assessee with any bank outside India with`
  line `the approval of the Reserve Bank of India.`
  line `3 [Explanation 2. — For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression “competent authority” means`
  line `the Reserve Bank of India or such other authority as is authorised under any law for the time being in`
  line `force for regulating payments and dealings in foreign exchange.]`
  line `( 3 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), profits derived from the business referred to in that sub-`
  line `section shall be the amount which bears to the profits of the business, the same proportion as the export`
  line `turnover bears to the total turnover of the business carried on by the assessee.`
  line `4 [( 3A ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1A ), profits derived by a supporting software developer shall`
  line `be, —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the business carried on by the supporting software developer consists`
  line `exclusively of developing and selling of computer software to one or more exporting companies`
  line `solely engaged in exports, the profits of such business;`
  line `( ii ) in a case where the business carried on by a supporting software developer does not consist`
  line `exclusively of developing and selling of computer software to one or more exporting companies, the`
  line `amount which bears to the profits of the business, the same proportion as the turnover in respect of`
  line `sale to the respective exporting company bears to the total turnover of the business carried on by the`
  line assessee.]
  line `( 4 ) The deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall not be admissible unless the assessee furnishes in the`
  line `prescribed form, along with the return of income, the report of an accountant, as defined in`
  line `the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288, certifying that the deduction has been correctly`
  line `claimed in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line `4 [( 4A ) The deduction under sub-section ( 1A ) shall not be admissible unless the supporting software`
  line `developer furnishes in the prescribed form along with his return of income, —`
  line `( i ) the report of an accountant, as defined in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288,`
  line `certifying that the deduction has been correctly claimed on the basis of the profits of the supporting`
  line `software developer in respect of sale of computer software to the exporting company; and`
  line `( ii ) a certificate from the exporting company containing such particulars as may be prescribed and`
  line `verified in the manner prescribed that in respect of the export turnover mentioned in the certificate,`
  line `the exporting company has not claimed deduction under this section:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s.48, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `2. Explanation relettered as Explanation 1 thereof by s. 48, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-1999)`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 48, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s.33 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_376_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_377:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-377
  sectionNo (377)
