  title `Page 377`
  content obj_root_law_sections_377_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_377_footnotes
  sourcePage 377
obj_root_law_sections_377_content:
  string
  line 377
  line `Provided that the certificate specified in clause ( b ) shall be duly certified by the auditor auditing the`
  line `accounts of the exporting assessee under the provisions of this Act or under any other law.]`
  line `( 5 ) Where a deduction under this section is claimed and allowed in respect of profits of the business`
  line `referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) for any assessment year, no deduction shall be allowed in relation to such`
  line `profits under any other provision of this Act for the same or any other assessment year.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “convertible foreign exchange” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( a ) of`
  line `the Explanation to section 80HHC;`
  line `1 [( b ) “computer software” means,—`
  line `( i ) any computer programme recorded on any disc, tape, perforated media or other`
  line `information storage device; or`
  line `( ii ) anycustomised electronic data or any product or service of similar nature as may be`
  line `notified by the Board,`
  line `which is transmitted or exported from India to a place outside India by any means;]`
  line `( c ) “export turnover” means the consideration in respect of computer software received in, or`
  line `brought into, India by the assessee in convertible foreign exchange in accordance with sub-section`
  line `( 2 ), but does not include freight, telecommunication charges or insurance attributable to the delivery`
  line `of the computer software outside India or expenses, if any, incurred in foreign exchange in providing`
  line `the technical services outside India;`
  line `1 [( ca ) “exporting company” means a company re ferred to in sub-section ( 1 ) making actual export`
  line `of computer software;]`
  line `( d ) “profits of the business” means the profits of the business as computed under the head “Profits`
  line `and gains of business or profession” as reduced by—`
  line `( 1 ) ninety per cent of any receipts by way of brokerage, commission, interest, rent, charges or`
  line `any other receipt of a similar nature included in such profits; and`
  line `( 2 ) the profits of any branch, office, warehouse or any other establishment of the assessee`
  line `situate outside India;]`
  line `( e ) “total turnover” shall not include—`
  line `( i ) any sum referred to in clauses ( iiia ), ( iiib ) and ( iiic ) of section 28;`
  line `( ii ) any freight, telecommunication charges or insurance attributable to the delivery of the`
  line `computer software outside India; and`
  line `( iii ) expenses, if any, incurred in foreign exchange in providing the technical services`
  line `outside India;]`
  line `2 [( ea ) “supporting software developer” means an Indian company or a person (other than a`
  line `company) resident in India, developing and selling computer software to an exporting company for`
  line `the purposes of export.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 36, for sub-clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_377_footnotes:
