  title `Page 378`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_378_footnotes
  sourcePage 378
obj_root_law_sections_378_content:
  string
  line 378
  line `1 [80HHF. Deduction in respect of profits and gains from export or transfer of film software,`
  line `etc. — ( 1 ) Where an assessee, being an Indian company 2 [or a person (other than a company) resident in`
  line `India], is engaged in the business of export or transfer by any means out of India, of any film software,`
  line `television software, music software, television news software, including telecast rights (hereafter in this`
  line `section referred to as the software or software rights), there shall, in accordance with and subject to the`
  line `provisions of this section, be allowed, in computing the total income of the assessee, 3 [a deduction to the`
  line `extent of profits, referred to in sub-section ( 1A ),] derived by the assessee from such business.`
  line `4 [( 1A ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), the extent of deduction of profits shall be an amount equal`
  line `to —`
  line `( i ) eighty per cent. of such profits for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2001;`
  line `5 [( ii ) seventy per cent. thereof for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2002;`
  line `( iii ) fifty per cent. thereof for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2003;`
  line `( iv ) thirty per cent. thereof for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2004,]`
  line `and no deduction shall be allowed in respect of the assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April,`
  line `2005 and any subsequent assessment year.`
  line `( 2 ) The deduction specified in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be allowed only if the consideration in respect of`
  line `the software or software rights referred to in that sub-section is received in, or brought into, India by the`
  line `assessee in convertible foreign exchange, within a period of six months from the end of the previous year`
  line `or within such further period as the competent authority may allow in this behalf.`
  line `( 3 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), profits derived from the business referred to in that sub-`
  line `section shall be the amount which bears to the profits of the business, the same proportion as the export`
  line `turnover bears to the total turnover of the business carried on by the assessee.`
  line `( 4 ) The deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall not be admissible unless the assessee furnishes in the`
  line `prescribed form, along with the return of income, the report of an accountant, as defined in`
  line `the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of setion 288, certifying that the deduction has been correctly`
  line `claimed in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line `( 5 ) Where a deduction under this section is claimed and allowed in respect of profits of the business`
  line `referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) for any assessment year, no deduction shall be allowed in relation to such`
  line `profits under any other provision of this Act for the same or any other assessment year.`
  line `( 6 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, no deduction shall be allowed in respect of the`
  line `software or software rights referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), if such business is prohibited by any law for the`
  line `time being in force.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “competent authority” means the Reserve Bank of India or such other authority as is`
  line `authorised under any law for the time being in force for regulating payments and dealings in foreign`
  line exchange;
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s.49 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 37, ibid., for “a deduction of the profits” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2001).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 37, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 43, for clauses ( ii ), ( iii ) and ( iv ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
