obj_root_law_sections_379_content:
  string
  line 379
  line `( b ) “convertible foreign exchange” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( a ) of`
  line `the Explanation to section 80HHC;`
  line `( c ) “export turnover” means the consideration in respect of the software or software rights`
  line `specified in clauses ( d ), ( e ), ( g ), ( h ) and (i ), received in, or brought into, India by the assessee in`
  line `convertible foreign exchange in accordance with sub-section ( 2 ), but does not include freight,`
  line `telecommunication charges or insurance attributable to the delivery of such software outside India or`
  line `expenses, if any, incurred in foreign exchange in providing the technical services outside India;`
  line `( d ) “film software” means a copy of a cinematograph film made by any process analogous to`
  line `cinematography on acetate polyester or celluloid film positive, magnetic tape, digital media or other`
  line `optical or magnetic devices and certified by the Board of film certification constituted by the Central`
  line `Government under section 3 of the Cinematograph Act, 1952 (37 of 1952);`
  line `( e ) “music software”includes series of sounds or music recorded on magnetic tape, cassette,`
  line `compact discs and digital media which can be played or reproduced on any appropriate apparatus;`
  line `( f ) “profits of the business” means the profits of the business as computed under the head “Profits`
  line `and gains of business or profession” as reduced by—`
  line `( A ) ninety per cent of any receipts by way of brokerage, commission, interest, rent, charges or`
  line `any other receipt of a similar nature included in such profits; and`
  line `( B ) the profits of any branch, office, warehouse or any other establishment of the assessee`
  line `situated outside India;`
  line `( g ) “telecast rights” means a licence or contract to exhibit motion pictures or television`
  line `programmes over a television network either through terrestrial transmission or through a satellite`
  line `broadcast in a specified territory;`
  line `( h ) “television news software” means a collect ion of sounds and images, reportage, data and`
  line `voice of actualities broadcast either through terrestrial transmission, wire or satellite, live or`
  line `pre-recorded on video cassettes or digital media;`
  line `( i ) “television software” means any program me or series of sounds and images recorded on film`
  line `or tape or digital media or broadcast through terrestrial transmitter, satellite or any other means of`
  line diffusion;
  line `( j ) “total turnover” shall not include—`
  line `( A ) any sum referred to in clauses ( iiia ), ( iiib ) and ( iiic ) of section 28;`
  line `( B ) any freight, telecommunication charges or insurance attributable to the delivery of the`
  line `film software, music software, telecast rights, television news software, or television software as`
  line `defined in clause ( d ), ( e ), ( g ), ( h ) or ( i ), as the case may be, outside India;`
  line `( C ) expenses, if any, incurred in foreign exchange in providing the technical services outside`
  line India.]
obj_root_law_sections_379_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_380:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-380
  sectionNo (380)
