  title `Page 380`
  content obj_root_law_sections_380_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_380_footnotes
  sourcePage 380
obj_root_law_sections_380_content:
  string
  line 380
  line `1 [ 80-I. Deduction in respect of profits and gains from industrial undertakings after a certain`
  line `date, etc. — ( 1 ) Where the gross total income of an assessee includes any profits and gains derived from`
  line `an industrial undertaking or a ship or the business of a hotel 2 [or the business of repairs to ocean-going`
  line `vessels or other powered craft], to which this section applies, there shall, in accordance with and subject`
  line `to the provisions of this section, be allowed, in computing the total income of the assessee, a deduction`
  line `from such profits and gains of an amount equal to twenty per cent. thereof:`
  line `Provided that in the case of an assessee, being a company, the provisions of this sub-section 3 [shall`
  line `have effect in relation to profits and gains derived from an industrial undertaking or a ship or the business`
  line `of a hotel] as if for the words “twenty per cent.”, the words “twenty - five per cent.” had been substituted.`
  line `4 [( 1A ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), in relation to any profits and gains`
  line `derived by an assessee from —`
  line `( i ) an industrial undertaking which begins to manufacture or produce articles or things or to`
  line `operate its cold storage plant or plants; or`
  line `( ii ) a ship which is first brought into use; or`
  line `( iii ) the business of a hotel which starts functioning,`
  line `on or after the 1st day of April, 1990, 5 [but before the 1st day of April, 1991], there shall, in accordance`
  line `with and subject to the provisions of this section, be allowed in computing the total income of the`
  line `assessee, a deduction from such profits and gains of an amount equal to twenty-five per cent. thereof:`
  line `Provided that in the case of an assessee, being a company, the provisions of this sub-section shall`
  line `have effect in relation to profits and gains derived from an industrial undertaking or a ship or the business`
  line `of a hotel as if for the words “twenty - five per cent.”, the words “thirty per cent.” had bee n substituted.]`
  line `( 2 ) This section applies to any industrial undertaking which fulfils all the following conditions,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( i ) it is not formed by the splitting up, or the reconstruction, of a business already in existence;`
  line `( ii ) it is not formed by the transfer to a new business of machinery or plant previously used for`
  line `any purpose;`
  line `( iii ) it manufactures or produces any article or thing, not being any article or thing specified in the`
  line `list in the Eleventh Schedule, or operates one or more cold storage plant or plants, in any part of`
  line `India, and begins to manufacture or produce articles or things or to operate such plant or plants, at any`
  line `time within the period of 6 [ten years] next following the 31st day of March, 1981, or such further`
  line `period as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify with reference`
  line `to any particular industrial undertaking;`
  line `( iv ) in a case where the industrial undertaking manufactures or produces articles or things, the`
  line `undertaking employs ten or more workers in a manufacturing process carried on with the aid of`
  line `power, or employs twenty or more workers in a manufacturing process carried on without the aid of`
  line `power:`
  line `Provided that the condition in clause ( i ) shall not apply in respect of any industrial undertaking`
  line `which is formed as a result of the re-establishment, reconstruction or revival by the assessee of the`
  line `business of any such industrial undertaking as is referred to in section 33B, in the circumstances and`
  line `within the period specified in that section:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-1981).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 11 of 1983, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-4-1984).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 25, ibid., for “shall have effect” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1984).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `6. Subs. by, s. 31, ibid., for “fourteen years” (w.e.f. 1 -4- 1991). Earlier “fourteen years” was subs. for “nine years” by`
  line `Act 12 of 1990 s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-1990) which was earlier su bs. for “four years” by Act 32 of 1985, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_380_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_381:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-381
  sectionNo (381)
  orderNo 381
  title `Page 381`
  content obj_root_law_sections_381_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_381_footnotes
  sourcePage 381
obj_root_law_sections_381_content:
  string
  line 381
  line `Provided further that the condition in clause ( iii ) shall, in relation to a small-scale industrial`
  line `undertaking, apply as if the words “not being any article or thing specified in the list in the Eleventh`
  line `Schedule” had been omitted.`
  line `Explanation 1. — For the purposes of clause ( ii ) of this sub-section, any machinery or plant which was`
  line `used outside India by any person other than the assessee shall not be regarded as machinery or plant`
  line `previously used for any purpose, if the following conditions are fulfilled, namely: —`
  line `( a ) such machinery or plant was not, at any time previous to the date of the installation by the`
  line `assessee, used in India;`
  line `( b ) such machinery or plant is imported into India from any country outside India; and`
  line `( c ) no deduction on account of depreciation in respect of such machinery or plant has been`
  line `allowed or is allowable under the provisions of this Act in computing the total income of any person`
  line `for any period prior to the date of the installation of the machinery or plant by the assessee.`
  line `Explanation 2. — Where in the case of an industrial undertaking, any machinery or plant or any part`
  line `thereof previously used for any purpose is transferred to a new business and the total value of the`
  line `machinery or plant or part so transferred does not exceed twenty per cent of the total value of the`
  line `machinery or plant used in the business, then, for the purposes of clause ( ii ) of this sub-section, the`
  line `condition specified therein shall be deemed to have been complied with.`
  line `Explanation 3. — For the purposes of this sub- section, “small - scale industrial undertaking” shall have`
  line `the same meaning as in clause ( b ) of the Explanation below sub-section ( 8 ) of section 80HHA.`
  line `( 3 ) This section applies to any ship, where all the following conditions are fulfilled, namely: —`
  line `( i ) it is owned by an Indian company and is wholly used for the purposes of the business carried`
  line `on by it;`
  line `( ii ) it was not, previous to the date of its acquisition by the Indian company, owned or used in`
  line `Indian territorial waters by a person resident in India; and`
  line `( iii ) it is brought into use by the Indian company at any time within the period of 1 [ten years] next`
  line `following the 1st day of April, 1981.`
  line `( 4 ) This section applies to the business of any hotel, where all the following conditions are fulfilled,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( i ) the business of the hotel is not formed by the splitting up, or the reconstruction, of a business`
  line `already in existence or by the transfer to a new business of a building previously used as a hotel or of`
  line `any machinery or plant previously used for any purpose;`
  line `( ii ) the business of the hotel is owned and carried on by a company registered in India with a`
  line `paid-up capital of not less than five hundred thousand rupees;`
  line `( iii ) the hotel is for the time being approved for the purposes of this sub-section by the Central`
  line Government;
  line `( iv ) the business of the hotel starts functioning after the 31st day of March, 1981, but 2 [before the`
  line `1st day of April, 3 [1991]].`
  line `1. Subs. by 49 of 1991, s. 31, for “fourteen years” (w.e.f. 1 -4- 1991). Earlier “fourteen years” was subs. for “nine years” by`
  line `Act 12 of 1990 s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-19 90) which was earlier substituted for “four years” by Act 32 of 1985,`
  line `s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 24, for “before the first day of April, 1990” (w.e.f. 1 -4- 1990). Earlier “1990” was substituted`
  line `for “1985” by 32 of 1985, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1985).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 31, for “1995” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_381_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_382:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-382
  sectionNo (382)
