  title `Page 382`
  content obj_root_law_sections_382_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_382_footnotes
  sourcePage 382
obj_root_law_sections_382_content:
  string
  line 382
  line `1 [( 4A ) This section applies to the business of repairs to ocean-going vessels or other powered craft`
  line `which fulfils all the following conditions, namely: —`
  line `( i ) the business is not formed by the splitting up, or the reconstruction, of a business already in`
  line existence;
  line `( ii ) it is not formed by the transfer to a new business of machinery or plant previously used for`
  line `any purpose;`
  line `( iii ) it is carried on by an Indian company and the work by way of repairs to ocean-going vessels`
  line `or other powered craft has been commenced by such company after the 31st day of March, 1983, but`
  line `before the 1st day of April, 1988; and`
  line `( iv ) it is for the time being approved for the purposes of this sub-section by the Central`
  line Government.]
  line `( 5 ) The deduction specified in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be allowed in computing the total income in`
  line `respect of the assessment year relevant to the previous year in which the industrial undertaking begins to`
  line `manufacture or produce articles or things, or to operate its cold storage plant or plants or the ship is first`
  line `brought into use or the business of the hotel starts functioning 1 [or the company commences work by way`
  line `of repairs to ocean-going vessels or other powered craft] (such assessment year being hereafter in this`
  line `section referred to as the initial assessment year) and each of the seven assessment years immediately`
  line `succeeding the initial assessment year:`
  line `Provided that in the case of an assessee, being a co-operative society, the provisions of this`
  line `sub- section shall have effect as if for the words “seven assessment years”, the words “nine assessment`
  line `years” had been substituted:`
  line `1 [Provided further that in the case of an assessee carrying on the business of repairs to ocean-going`
  line `vessels or other powered craft, the provisions of this sub-section shall have effect as if for the words`
  line `“seven assessment years”, the words “four assessment years” had been substituted]:`
  line `2 [Provided also that in the case of —`
  line `( i ) an industrial undertaking which begins to manufacture or produce articles or things or to`
  line `operate its cold storage plant or plants; or`
  line `( ii ) a ship which is first brought into use; or`
  line `( iii ) the business of a hotel which starts functioning,`
  line `on or after the 1st day of April, 1990 3 [but before the 1st day of April, 1991], provisions of this`
  line `sub-section shall have effect as if for the words “seven assessment years”, the words “nine assessment`
  line `years” had been substituted:`
  line `Provided also that in the case of an assessee, being a co-operative society, deriving profits and gains`
  line `from an industrial undertaking or a ship or a hotel referred to in the third proviso, the provisions of that`
  line `proviso shall have effect as if for the words “nine assessment years”, the words “eleven assessment years”`
  line `had been substituted.]`
  line `( 6 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, the profits and gains of an`
  line `industrial undertaking or a ship or the business of a hotel 1 [or the business of repairs to ocean-going`
  line `vessels or other powered craft] to which the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) apply shall, for the purposes of`
  line `determining the quantum of deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) for the assessment year immediately`
  line `succeeding the initial assessment year or any subsequent assessment year, be computed as if such`
  line `industrial undertaking or ship or the business of the hotel 1 [or the business of repairs to ocean-going`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1983, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-4-1984).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_382_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_383:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-383
  sectionNo (383)
  orderNo 383
  title `Page 383`
  content obj_root_law_sections_383_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_383_footnotes
  sourcePage 383
obj_root_law_sections_383_content:
  string
  line 383
  line `vessels or other powered craft] were the only source of income of the assessee during the previous years`
  line `relevant to the initial assessment year and to every subsequent assessment year up to and including the`
  line `assessment year for which the determination is to be made.`
  line `( 7 ) Where the assessee is a person other than a company or a co-operative society, the deduction`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) from profits and gains derived from an industrial undertaking shall not be`
  line `admissible unless the accounts of the industrial undertaking for the previous year relevant to the`
  line `assessment year for which the deduction is claimed have been audited by an accountant, as defined in`
  line `the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288, and the assessee furnishes, along with his return of`
  line `income, the report of such audit in the prescribed form duly signed and verified by such accountant.`
  line `( 8 ) Where any goods held for the purposes of the business of the industrial undertaking or the hotel or`
  line `the operation of the ship 1 [or the business of repairs to ocean-going vessels or other powered craft] are`
  line `transferred to any other business carried on by the assessee, or where any goods held for the purposes of`
  line `any other business carried on by the assessee are transferred to the business of the industrial undertaking`
  line `or the hotel or the operation of the ship 1 [or the business of repairs to ocean-going vessels or other`
  line `powered craft] and, in either case, the consideration, if any, for such transfer as recorded in the accounts`
  line `of the business of the industrial undertaking or the hotel or the operation of the ship 1 [or the business of`
  line `repairs to ocean-going vessels or other powered craft] does not correspond to the market value of such`
  line `goods as on the date of the transfer, then, for the purposes of the deduction under this section, the profits`
  line `and gains of the industrial undertaking or the business of the hotel or the operation of the ship 1 [or the`
  line `business of repairs to ocean-going vessels or other powered craft shall be computed as if the transfer, in`
  line `either case, had been made at the market value of such goods as on that date:`
  line `Provided that where, in the opinion of the 2 [Assessing Officer], the computation of the profits and`
  line `gains of the industrial undertaking or the business of the hotel or the operation of the ship 1 [or the`
  line `business of repairs to ocean-going vessels or other powered craft] in the manner hereinbefore specified`
  line `presents exceptional difficulties, the 2 [Assessing Officer] may compute such profits and gains on such`
  line `reasonable basis as he may deem fit.`
  line `Explanation. — In this sub- section, “market value”, in relation to any goods, means the price that such`
  line `goods would ordinarily fetch on sale in the open market.`
  line `( 9 ) Where it appears to the 2 [Assessing Officer] that, owing to the close connection between the`
  line `assessee carrying on the business of the industrial undertaking or the hotel or the operation of the ship 1 [or`
  line `the business of repairs to ocean-going vessels or other powered craft] to which this section applies and`
  line `any other person, or for any other reason, the course of business between them is so arranged that the`
  line `business transacted between them produces to the assessee more than the ordinary profits which might be`
  line `expected to arise in the business of the industrial undertaking or the hotel or the operation of the ship 1 [or`
  line `the business of repairs to ocean-going vessels or other powered craft], the 2 [Assessing Officer] shall, in`
  line `computing the profits and gains of the industrial undertaking or the hotel or the ship 1 [or the business of`
  line `repairs to ocean-going vessels or other powered craft] for the purposes of the deduction under this section,`
  line `take the amount of profits as may be reasonably deemed to have been derived therefrom.`
  line `( 10 ) The Central Government may, after making such inquiry as it may think fit, direct, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, that the exemption conferred by this section shall not apply to any`
  line `class of industrial undertakings with effect from such date as it may specify in the notification.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1983, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-4-1984).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_383_footnotes:
