  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_384_footnotes
  sourcePage 384
obj_root_law_sections_384_content:
  string
  line 384
  line `1 [80-IA. Deductions in respect of profits and gains from industrial undertakings or enterprises`
  line `engaged in infrastructure development, etc. — 2 [( 1 ) Where the gross total income of an assessee`
  line `includes any profits and gains derived by an undertaking or an enterprise from any business referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 4 ) (such business being hereinafter referred to as the eligible business), there shall, in`
  line `accordance with and subject to the provisions of this section, be allowed, in computing the total income of`
  line `the assessee, a deduction of an amount equal to hundred per cent. of the profits and gains derived from`
  line `such business for ten consecutive assessment years.]`
  line `( 2 ) The deduction specified in sub-section ( 1 ) may, at the option of the assessee, be claimed by him`
  line `for any ten consecutive assessment years out of fifteen years beginning from the year in which the`
  line `undertaking or the enterprise develops and begins to operate any infrastructure facility or starts providing`
  line `telecommunication service or develops an industrial park 3 [ 4 [or develops a special economic zone`
  line `referred to in clause ( iii ) of sub-section ( 4 )]] or generates power or commences transmission or`
  line `distribution of power 5 [or undertakes substantial renovation and modernisation of the existing`
  line `transmission or distribution lines 6 ***]:`
  line `7 [Provided that where the assessee develops or operates and maintains or develops, operates and`
  line `maintains any infrastructure facility referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ) of`
  line `the Explanation to clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 4 ), the provisions of this sub-section shall have effect as if for`
  line `the words “fifteen years”, the words “twenty years” had been substituted.]`
  line `8 [( 2A ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ), the deduction in`
  line `computing the total income of an undertaking providing telecommunication services, specified in clause`
  line `( ii ) of sub-section ( 4 ), shall be hundred per cent of the profits and gains of the eligible business for the`
  line `first five assessment years commencing at any time during the periods as specified in sub-section ( 2 ) and`
  line `thereafter, thirty per cent of such profits and gains for further five assessment years.]`
  line `( 3 ) This section applies to 9 [an 10 [ 11 [undertaking] referred to in clause ( ii ) 12 [or clause ( iv ) 13 ***] of`
  line `sub-section ( 4 )] which fulfils all the following conditions, namely: —`
  line `( i ) it is not formed by splitting up, or the reconstruction, of a business already in existence:`
  line `Provided that this condition shall not apply in respect of an 10 [undertaking] which is formed as a`
  line `result of the re-establishment, reconstruction or revival by the assessee of the business of any such`
  line `10 [undertaking] as is referred to in section 33B, in the circumstances and within the period specified in`
  line `that section;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 50, for section 80-IA (w.e.f. 1-4-2000), earlier inserted by Act 49 of 1991, s. 32`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1991), and later on amended by Act 18 of 1992, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993), which was earlier amended by Act 38`
  line `of 1993, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-1994), earlier amended by Act 32 of 1994, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-1994), earlier amended by Act 22`
  line `of 1995, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-1996), amended by Act 38 of 1996, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-1997), amended by Act 26 of 1997, s. 26`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1996), as so amended by Act 7 of 1998, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998), amended by Act 21 of 1998, s. 34`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 44, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 38 for “or develops or develops and operates or maintains and operates a special economi c`
  line `zone” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2002).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
  line `6. The words “or lays and begins to operate a cross - country natural gas distribution network” omitted by Act 33 of 2009,`
  line `s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `7. The proviso substituted by Act 14 of 2001, s. 44 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `8. Ins. by s. 44, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 38, for “any industrial undertaking “ (w.e.f. 1 -4-2000).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 44, for “industrial undertaking” (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 17, for “undertaking referred to in clause ( iv )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2005).`
  line `12. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 28, for “clause ( iv )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2008).`
  line `13. The words, brackets and figures “or clause ( vi )” omitted by Act 33 of 2009, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
