obj_root_law_sections_385_content:
  string
  line 385
  line `( ii ) it is not formed by the transfer to a new business of machinery or plant previously used for`
  line `any purpose:`
  line `1 [Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply in the case of transfer, either in`
  line `whole or in part, of machinery or plant previously used by a State Electricity Board referred to in clause`
  line `( 7 ) of section 2 of the Electricity Act, 2003 (36 of 2003), whether or not such transfer is in pursuance of`
  line `the splitting up or reconstruction or reorganisation of the Board under Part XIII of that Act.]`
  line `Explanation 1. — For the purposes of clause ( ii ), any machinery or plant which was used outside India`
  line `by any person other than the assessee shall not be regarded as machinery or plant previously used for any`
  line `purpose, if the following conditions are fulfilled, namely: —`
  line `( a ) such machinery or plant was not, at any time previous to the date of the installation by the`
  line `assessee, used in India;`
  line `( b ) such machinery or plant is imported into India from any country outside India; and`
  line `( c ) no deduction on account of depreciation in respect of such machinery or plant has been`
  line `allowed or is allowable under the provisions of this Act in computing the total income of any person`
  line `for any period prior to the date of the installation of machinery or plant by the assessee.`
  line `Explanation 2. — Where in the case of an 2 [undertaking], any machinery or plant or any part thereof`
  line `previously used for any purpose is transferred to a new business and the total value of the machinery or`
  line `plant or part so transferred does not exceed twenty per cent of the total value of the machinery or plant`
  line `used in the business, then, for the purposes of clause ( ii ) of this sub-section, the condition specified`
  line `therein shall be deemed to have been complied with.`
  line `( 4 ) This section applies to —`
  line `( i ) any enterprise carrying on the business 3 [of ( i ) developing or ( ii ) operating and maintaining`
  line `or ( iii ) developing, operating and maintaining] any infrastructure facility which fulfils all the`
  line `following conditions, namely: —`
  line `( a ) it is owned by a company registered in India or by a consortium of such companies 4 [or`
  line `by an authority or a board or a corporation or any other body established or constituted under any`
  line `Central or State Act]:`
  line `5 [( b ) it has entered into an agreement with the Central Government or a State Government or`
  line `a local authority or any other statutory body for ( i ) developing or ( ii ) operating and maintaining`
  line `or ( iii ) developing, operating and maintaining a new infrastructure facility;]`
  line `( c ) it has started or starts operating and maintaining the infrastructure facility on or after the`
  line `1st day of April, 1995:`
  line `Provided that where an infrastructure facility is transferred on or after the 1st day`
  line `of April, 1999 by an enterprise which developed such infrastructure facility (hereafter`
  line `referred to in this section as the transferor enterprise) to another enterprise (hereafter in this`
  line `section referred to as the transferee enterprise) for the purpose of operating and maintaining the`
  line `infrastructure facility on its behalf in accordance with the agreement with the Central`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 44, for “industrial undertaking” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2002).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 44, ibid., for “of ( i ) developing, ( ii ) maintaining and operating or ( iii ) developing, maintaining and operating”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 44, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
