obj_root_law_sections_386_content:
  string
  line 386
  line `Government, State Government, local authority or statutory body, the provisions of this section`
  line `shall apply to the transferee enterprise as if it were the enterprise to which this clause applies and`
  line `the deduction from profits and gains would be available to such transferee enterprise for the`
  line `unexpired period during which the transferor enterprise would have been entitled to the`
  line `deduction, if the transfer had not taken place:`
  line `1 [Provided further that nothing contained in this section shall apply to any enterprise which`
  line `starts the development or operation and maintenance of the infrastructure facility on or after the`
  line `1st day of April, 2017.]`
  line `2 [ Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, “infrastructure facility” means—`
  line `( a ) a road including toll road, a bridge or a rail system;`
  line `( b ) a highway project including housing or other activities being an integral part of the`
  line `highway project;`
  line `( c ) a water supply project, water treatment system, irrigation project, sanitation and sewerage`
  line `system or solid waste management system;`
  line `( d ) a port, airport, inland waterway 3 [, inland port or navigational channel in the sea];]`
  line `4 [( ii ) any undertaking which has started or starts providing telecommunication services, whether`
  line `basic or cellular, including radio paging, domestic satellite service, network of trunking, broadband`
  line `network and internet services on or after the 1st day of April, 1995, but on or before the 5 [31st day of`
  line `March, 2005].]`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, “domestic satellite” means a satellite owned and`
  line `operated by an Indian company for providing telecommunication service;`
  line `( iii ) any undertaking which develops, develops and operates or maintains and operates an`
  line `industrial park 6 [or special economic zone] notified by the Central Government in accordance with`
  line `the scheme framed and notified by that Government for the period beginning on the 1st day of April,`
  line `1997 and ending on 7 [the 31st day of March, 2006]:`
  line `8 [Provided that in a case where an undertaking develops an industrial park on or after the 1st day`
  line `of April, 1999 or a special economic zone on or after the 1st day of April, 2001 and transfers the`
  line `operation and maintenance of such industrial park or such special economic zone, as the case may be,`
  line `to another undertaking (hereafter in this section referred to as the transferee undertaking), the`
  line `deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be allowed to such transferee undertaking for the remaining`
  line `period in the ten consecutive assessment years as if the operation and maintenance were not so`
  line `transferred to the transferee undertaking:]`
  line `9 [Provided further that in the case of any undertaking which develops, develops and operates or`
  line `maintains and operates an industrial park, the provisions of this clause shall have effect as if for the`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 44, for Explanation (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 28, for “inland port” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2008).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 44, for clause ( ii ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 17, for “31st March, 2004” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2005).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 44, (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 44, ibid., for “the 31st March, 2002” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2001).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 38, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 18, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
