obj_root_law_sections_387_content:
  string
  line 387
  line `figures, letters and words “31st day of March, 2006”, the figures, letters and words 1 [31st day of`
  line `March, 2011] had been substituted;]`
  line `( iv ) an 2 [undertaking] which, —`
  line `( a ) is set up in any part of India for the generation or generation and distribution of power if`
  line `it begins to generate power at any time during the period beginning on the 1st day of April, 1993`
  line `and ending on 3 [the 31st day of March, 2017];`
  line `( b ) starts transmission or distribution by laying a network of new transmission or`
  line `distribution lines at any time during the period beginning on the 1st day of April, 1999 and`
  line `ending on 3 [the 31st day of March, 2017]:`
  line `Provided that the deduction under this section to an 2 [undertaking] under sub-clause (b ) shall be`
  line `allowed only in relation to the profits derived from laying of such network of new lines for transmission`
  line `or distribution;`
  line `4 [( c ) undertakes substantial renovation and modernisation of the existing network of transmission`
  line `or distribution lines at any time during the period beginning on the 1st day of April, 2004 and ending`
  line `on 3 [the 31st day of March, 2017].`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- clause, “substantial renovation and modernisation” means`
  line `an increase in the plant and machinery in the network of transmission or distribution lines by at least fifty`
  line `per cent of the book value of such plant and machinery as on the 1st day of April, 2004;]`
  line `5 [( v ) an undertaking owned by an Indian company and set up for reconstruction or revival of a`
  line `power generating plant, if —`
  line `( a ) such Indian company is formed before the 30th day of November, 2005 with majority`
  line `equity participation by public sector companies for the purposes of enforcing the security`
  line `interest of the lenders to the company owning the power generating plant and such Indian`
  line `company is notified before the 31st day of December, 2005 by the Central Government for the`
  line `purposes of this clause;`
  line `( b ) such undertaking begins to generate or transmit or distribute power before 6 [the 31st day`
  line `of March, 2011];]`
  line `7 * * * * *`
  line `( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, the profits and gains of an`
  line `eligible business to which the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) apply shall, for the purposes of determining`
  line `the quantum of deduction under that sub-section for the assessment year immediately succeeding the`
  line `initial assessment year or any subsequent assessment year, be computed as if such eligible business were`
  line `the only source of income of the assessee during the previous year relevant to the initial assessment year`
  line `and to every subsequent assessment year up to and including the assessment year for which the`
  line `determination is to be made.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 36, for “31st day of March, 2009” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2009).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 44, for “industrial undertaking” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2002).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 30, for “the 31st day of March, 2014” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2015).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 17 (w.e.f 1-4-2005).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 55 of 2005, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 36, for “the 31st day of March, 2008” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2008).`
  line `7. Clause ( vi ) omitted by Act 33 of 2009, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_387_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_388:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-388
  sectionNo (388)
  orderNo 388
  title `Page 388`
  content obj_root_law_sections_388_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_388_footnotes
  sourcePage 388
obj_root_law_sections_388_content:
  string
  line 388
  line `( 6 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 4 ), where housing or other activities are an`
  line `integral part of the highway project and the profits of which are computed on such basis and manner as`
  line `may be prescribed, such profit shall not be liable to tax where the profit has been transferred to a special`
  line `reserve account and the same is actually utilised for the highway project excluding housing and other`
  line `activities before the expiry of three years following the year in which such amount was transferred to the`
  line `reserve account; and the amount remaining unutilised shall be chargeable to tax as income of the year in`
  line `which such transfer to reserve account took place.`
  line `( 7 ) 1 [The deduction] under sub-section ( 1 ) from profits and gains derived from an 2 [undertaking] shall`
  line `not be admissible unless the accounts of the 2 [undertaking] for the previous year relevant to the`
  line `assessment year for which the deduction is claimed have been audited by an accountant, as defined in`
  line `the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288, and the assessee furnishes, along with his return of`
  line `income, the report of such audit in the prescribed form duly signed and verified by such accountant.`
  line `( 8 ) Where any 3 [goods or services] held for the purposes of the eligible business are transferred to any`
  line `other business carried on by the assessee, or where any 3 [goods or services] held for the purposes of any`
  line `other business carried on by the assessee are transferred to the eligible business and, in either case, the`
  line `consideration, if any, for such transfer as recorded in the accounts of the eligible business does not`
  line `correspond to the market value of such 3 [goods or services] as on the date of the transfer, then, for the`
  line `purposes of the deduction under this section, the profits and gains of such eligible business shall be`
  line `computed as if the transfer, in either case, had been made at the market value of such 3 [goods or services]`
  line `as on that date:`
  line `Provided that where, in the opinion of the Assessing Officer, the computation of the profits and gains`
  line `of the eligible business in the manner hereinbefore specified presents exceptional difficulties, the`
  line `Assessing Officer may compute such profits and gains on such reasonable basis as he may deem fit.`
  line `4 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- section, “market value”, in relation to any goods or`
  line `services, means —`
  line `( i ) the price that such goods or services would ordinarily fetch in the open market; or`
  line `( ii ) the arm’s length price as defined in clause ( ii ) of section 92F, where the transfer of such`
  line `goods or services is a specified domestic transaction referred to in section 92BA.]`
  line `( 9 ) Where any amount of profits and gains of an 2 [undertaking] or of an enterprise in the case of an`
  line `assessee is claimed and allowed under this section for any assessment year, deduction to the extent of`
  line `such profits and gains shall not be allowed un der any other provisions of this Chapter under the heading”`
  line `C. — Deductions in respect of certain incomes ”, and shall in no case exceed the profits and gains of such`
  line `eligible business of 2 [undertaking] or enterprise, as the case may be.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 33, for “Where the assessee is a person other than a company or a co -operative society, the`
  line `deduction” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2003).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 44, for “industrial undertaking” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2002).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 44, ibid., for “goods” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2002).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 30, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_388_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_389:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-389
  sectionNo (389)
  orderNo 389
  title `Page 389`
  content obj_root_law_sections_389_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_389_footnotes
  sourcePage 389
obj_root_law_sections_389_content:
  string
  line 389
  line `( 10 ) Where it appears to the Assessing Officer that, owing to the close connection between the`
  line `assessee carrying on the eligible business to which this section applies and any other person, or for any`
  line `other reason, the course of business between them is so arranged that the business transacted between`
  line `them produces to the assessee more than the ordinary profits which might be expected to arise in such`
  line `eligible business, the Assessing Officer shall, in computing the profits and gains of such eligible business`
  line `for the purposes of the deduction under this section, take the amount of profits as may be reasonably`
  line `deemed to have been derived therefrom:`
  line `1 [Provided that in case the aforesaid arrangement involves a specified domestic transaction referred to`
  line `in section 92BA, the amount of profits from such transaction shall be determined having regard to arm’s`
  line `length price as defined in clause ( ii ) of section 92F.]`
  line `( 11 ) The Central Government may, after making such inquiry as it may think fit, direct, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, that the exemption conferred by this section shall not apply to any`
  line `class of industrial undertaking or enterprise with effect from such date as it may specify in the`
  line notification.
  line `( 12 ) Where any undertaking of an Indian company which is entitled to the deduction under this`
  line `section is transferred, before the expiry of the period specified in this section, to another Indian company`
  line `in a scheme of amalgamation or demerger —`
  line `( a ) no deduction shall be admissible under this section to the amalgamating or the demerged`
  line `company for the previous year in which the amalgamation or the demerger takes place; and`
  line `( b ) the provisions of this section shall, as far as may be, apply to the amalgamated or the`
  line `resulting company as they would have applied to the amalgamating or the demerged company if the`
  line `amalgamation or demerger had not taken place.`
  line `2 [( 12A ) Nothing contained in sub-section ( 12 ) shall apply to any enterprise or undertaking which is`
  line `transferred in a scheme of amalgamation or demerger on or after the 1st day of April, 2007.]`
  line `3 [( 13 ) Nothing contained in this section shall apply to any Special Economic Zones notified on or`
  line `after the 1st day of April, 2005 in accordance with the scheme referred to in sub-clause ( iii ) of clause ( c )`
  line `of sub-section ( 4 ).]`
  line `4 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that nothing contained in this section`
  line `shall apply in relation to a business referred to in sub-section ( 4 ) which is in the nature of a works`
  line `contract awarded by any person (including the Central or State Government) and executed by the`
  line `undertaking or enterprise referred to in sub-section ( 1 ).]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 28 of 2005, s. 27 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 10-2-2006).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_389_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_390:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-390
  sectionNo (390)
  orderNo 390
  title `Page 390`
  content obj_root_law_sections_390_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_390_footnotes
  sourcePage 390
obj_root_law_sections_390_content:
  string
  line 390
  line `1 [ 80-IAB. Deductions in respect of profits and gains by an undertaking or enterprise engaged in`
  line `development of Special Economic Zone. — ( 1 ) Where the gross total income of an assessee, being a`
  line `Developer, includes any profits and gains derived by an undertaking or an enterprise from any business of`
  line `developing a Special Economic Zone, notified on or after the 1st day of April, 2005 under the Special`
  line `Economic Zones Act, 2005, there shall, in accordance with and subject to the provisions of this section,`
  line `be allowed, in computing the total income of the assessee, a deduction of an amount equal to one hundred`
  line `per cent of the profits and gains derived from such business for ten consecutive assessment years.`
  line `2 [Provided that the provisions of this section shall not apply to an assessee, being a developer, where`
  line `the development of Special Economic Zone begins on or after the 1st day of April, 2017.]`
  line `( 2 ) The deduction specified in sub-section ( 1 ) may, at the option of the assessee, be claimed by him`
  line `for any ten consecutive assessment years out of fifteen years beginning from the year in which a Special`
  line `Economic Zone has been notified by the Central Government:`
  line `Provided that where in computing the total income of any undertaking, being a Developer for any`
  line `assessment year, its profits and gains had not been included by application of the provisions of`
  line `sub-section ( 13 ) of sectopm 80-IA, the undertaking being the Developer shall be entitled to deduction`
  line `referred to in this section only for the unexpired period of ten consecutive assessment years and thereafter`
  line `it shall be eligible for deduction from income as provided in sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ), as the case`
  line `may be:`
  line `Provided further that in a case where an undertaking, being a Developer who develops a Special`
  line `Economic Zone on or after the 1st day of April, 2005 and transfers the operation and maintenance of such`
  line `Special Economic Zone to another Developer (hereafter in this section referred to as the transferee`
  line `Developer), the deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be allowed to such transferee Developer for the`
  line `remaining period in the ten consecutive assessment years as if the operation and maintenance were not so`
  line `transferred to the transferee Developer.`
  line `( 3 ) The provisions of sub-section ( 5 ) and sub-sections ( 7 ) to ( 12 ) of section 80-JIA shall apply to the`
  line `Special Economic Zones for the purpose of allowing deductions under sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, “Developer” and “Special Economic Zone” shall have`
  line `the same meanings respectively as assigned to them in clauses ( g ) and ( za ) of section 2 of the Special`
  line `Economic Zones Act, 2005.]`
  line `3 [ 80-IAC. Special provision in respect of specified business. — ( 1 ) Where the gross total income of`
  line `an assessee, being an eligible start-up, includes any profits and gains derived from eligible business, there`
  line `shall, in accordance with and subject to the provisions of this section, be allowed, in computing the total`
  line `income of the assessee, a deduction of an amount equal to one hundred per cent of the profits and gains`
  line `derived from such business for three consecutive assessment years.`
  line `( 2 ) The deduction specified in sub-section ( 1 ) may, at the option of the assessee, be claimed by him`
  line `for any three consecutive assessment years out of 4 [seven years] beginning from the year in which the`
  line `eligible start-up is incorporated.`
  line `( 3 ) This section applies to a start-up which fulfils the following conditions, namely: —`
  line `( i ) it is not formed by splitting up, or the reconstruction, of a business already in existence:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2005, s. 27 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. l0-2-2006).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 42, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 36, for “five years” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_390_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_391:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-391
  sectionNo (391)
  orderNo 391
  title `Page 391`
  content obj_root_law_sections_391_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_391_footnotes
  sourcePage 391
obj_root_law_sections_391_content:
  string
  line 391
  line `Provided that this condition shall not apply in respect of a start-up which is formed as a result of`
  line `the re-establishment, reconstruction or revival by the assessee of the business of any such undertaking`
  line `as referred to in section 33B, in the circumstances and within the period specified in that section;`
  line `( ii ) it is not formed by the transfer to a new business of machinery or plant previously used for`
  line `any purpose.`
  line `Explanation 1. — For the purposes of this clause, any machinery or plant which was used outside India`
  line `by any person other than the assessee shall not be regarded as machinery or plant previously used for any`
  line `purpose, if all the following conditions are fulfilled, namely: —`
  line `( a ) such machinery or plant was not, at any time previous to the date of the installation by the`
  line `assessee, used in India;`
  line `( b ) such machinery or plant is imported into India;`
  line `( c ) no deduction on account of depreciation in respect of such machinery or plant has been`
  line `allowed or is allowable under the provisions of this Act in computing the total income of any person`
  line `for any period prior to the date of the installation of the machinery or plant by the assessee.`
  line `Explanation 2. — Where in the case of a start-up, any machinery or plant or any part thereof`
  line `previously used for any purpose is transferred to a new business and the total value of the machinery`
  line `or plant or part so transferred does not exceed twenty per cent of the total value of the machinery or`
  line `plant used in the business, then, for the purposes of clause ( ii ) of this sub-section, the condition`
  line `specified therein shall be deemed to have been complied with.`
  line `( 4 ) The provisions of sub-section ( 5 ) and sub-sections ( 7 ) to ( 11 ) of section 80-IA shall apply to the`
  line `start-ups for the purpose of allowing deductions under sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `1 [( i ) “eligible business” means a business carried out by an eligible start up engaged in`
  line `innovation, development or improvement of products or processes or services or a scalable business`
  line `model with a high potential of employment generation or wealth creation;]`
  line `( ii ) “eligible start - up” means a company or a limited liability partnership engaged in eligible`
  line `business which fulfils the following conditions, namely: —`
  line `( a ) it is incorporated on or after the 1st day of April, 2016 but before the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2 [2021];`
  line `( b ) the total turnover of its business does not exceed twenty-five crore rupees 3 [in the`
  line `previous year relevant to the assessment year for which deduction under sub-section (1) is`
  line `claimed]; and`
  line `( c ) it holds a certificate of eligible business from the Inter-Ministerial Board of Certification`
  line `as notified in the Official Gazette by the Central Government;`
  line `( iii ) “limited liability partnership” means a partnership referred to in clause ( n ) of sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 2 of the Limited Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009).]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 28, for clause ( i ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 28, ibid., for “2019” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2018).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 28, ibid., for “ in any of the previous years beginning on or after the 1st day of April, 2016 and ending on the`
  line `31st day of March, 2021 ” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_391_footnotes:
