obj_root_law_sections_392_content:
  string
  line 392
  line `80-IB. Deduction in respect of profits and gains from certain industrial undertakings other than`
  line `infrastructure development undertakings. — ( 1 ) Where the gross total income of an assessee includes`
  line `any profits and gains derived from any business referred to in sub-sections ( 3 ) to 1 [( 11 ), ( 11A ) and ( 11B )]`
  line `(such business being hereinafter referred to as the eligible business), there shall, in accordance with and`
  line `subject to the provisions of this section, be allowed, in computing the total income of the assessee, a`
  line `deduction from such profits and gains of an amount equal to such percentage and for such number of`
  line `assessment years as specified in this section.`
  line `( 2 ) This section applies to any industrial undertaking which fulfils all the following conditions,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( i ) it is not formed by splitting up, or the reconstruction, of a business already in existence:`
  line `Provided that this condition shall not apply in respect of an industrial undertaking which is`
  line `formed as a result of the re-establishment, reconstruction or revival by the assessee of the business of`
  line `any such industrial undertaking as is referred to in section 33B, in the circumstances and within the`
  line `period specified in that section;`
  line `( ii ) it is not formed by the transfer to a new business of machinery or plant previously used for`
  line `any purpose;`
  line `( iii ) it manufactures or produces any article or thing, not being any article or thing specified in the`
  line `list in the Eleventh Schedule, or operates one or more cold storage plant or plants, in any part of`
  line `India:`
  line `Provided that the condition in this clause shall, in relation to a small scale industrial undertaking`
  line `or an industrial undertaking referred to in sub-section ( 4 ) shall apply as if the words “not being any`
  line `article or thing specified in the list in the Eleventh Schedule” had been omitted.`
  line `Explanation 1. — For the purposes of clause ( ii ), any machinery or plant which was used outside`
  line `India by any person other than the assessee shall not be regarded as machinery or plant previously`
  line `used for any purpose, if the following conditions are fulfilled, namely: —`
  line `( a ) such machinery or plant was not, at any time previous to the date of the installation by the`
  line `assessee, used in India;`
  line `( b ) such machinery or plant is imported into India from any country outside India; and`
  line `( c ) no deduction on account of depreciation in respect of such machinery or plant has been`
  line `allowed or is allowable under the provisions of this Act in computing the total income of any`
  line `person for any period prior to the date of the installation of the machinery or plant by the`
  line assessee.
  line `Explanation 2. — Where in the case of an industrial undertaking, any machinery or plant or any`
  line `part thereof previously used for any purpose is transferred to a new business and the total value of the`
  line `machinery or plant or part so transferred does not exceed twenty per cent. of the total value of the`
  line `machinery or plant used in the business, then, for the purposes of clause ( ii ) of this sub-section, the`
  line `condition specified therein shall be deemed to have been complied with;`
  line `( iv ) in a case where the industrial undertaking manufactures or produces articles or things, the`
  line `undertaking employs ten or more workers in a manufacturing process carried on with the aid of`
  line `power, or employs twenty or more workers in a manufacturing process carried on without the aid of`
  line power.
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 18, for “( 11 ) and ( 11A )” (w.e.f. 1 -4- 2005). Earlier “( 3 ) to ( 11 ) and ( 11A )” subs. by Act 14 of`
  line `2001, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_392_footnotes:
