  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_393_footnotes
  sourcePage 393
obj_root_law_sections_393_content:
  string
  line 393
  line `( 3 ) The amount of deduction in the case of an industrial undertaking shall be twenty-five per cent. (or`
  line `thirty per cent. where the assessee is a company), of the profits and gains derived from such industrial`
  line `undertaking for a period of ten consecutive assessment years (or twelve consecutive assessment years`
  line `where the assessee is a co-operative society) beginning with the initial assessment year subject to the`
  line `fulfilment of the following conditions, namely: —`
  line `( i ) it begins to manufacture or produce, articles or things or to operate such plant or plants at any`
  line `time during the period beginning from the 1st day of April, 1991 and ending on the 31st day of`
  line `March, 1995 or such further period as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify with reference to any particular undertaking;`
  line `( ii ) where it is an industrial undertaking being a small scale industrial undertaking, it begins to`
  line `manufacture or produce articles or things or to operate its cold storage plant [not specified in`
  line `sub-section ( 4 ) or sub-section ( 5 )] at any time during the period beginning on the 1st day of April,`
  line `1995 and ending on the 1 [31st day of March, 2002].`
  line `( 4 ) The amount of deduction in the case of an industrial undertaking in an industrially backward State`
  line `specified in the Eighth Schedule shall be hundred per cent of the profits and gains derived from such`
  line `industrial undertaking for five assessment years beginning with the initial assessment year and thereafter`
  line `twenty-five per cent. (or thirty per cent. where the assessee is a company) of the profits and gains derived`
  line `from such industrial undertaking:`
  line `Provided that the total period of deduction does not exceed ten consecutive assessment years (or`
  line `twelve consecutive assessment years where the assessee is a co-operative society) subject to fulfilment of`
  line `the condition that it begins to manufacture or produce articles or things or to operate its cold storage plant`
  line `or plants during the period beginning on the 1st day of April, 1993 and ending on the 2 [31st day of March,`
  line `2004]:`
  line `Provided further that in the case of such industries in the North-Eastern Region, as may be notified by`
  line `the Central Government, the amount of deduction shall be hundred per cent. of profits and gains for a`
  line `period of ten assessment years, and the total period of deduction shall in such a case not exceed ten`
  line `assessment years:`
  line `3 [Provided also that no deduction under this sub-section shall be allowed for the assessment year`
  line `beginning on the 1st day of April, 2004 or any subsequent year to any undertaking or enterprise referred`
  line `to in sub-section ( 2 ) of section 80-IC:]`
  line `4 [Provided also that in the case of an industrial undertaking in the State of Jammu and Kashmir, the`
  line `provisions of the first proviso shall have effect as if for the figures, letters and words “31st day of March,`
  line `2004”, the figures, letters and words 5 [31st day of March, 2012] had been substituted:`
  line `Provided also that no deduction under this sub-section shall be allowed to an industrial undertaking in`
  line `the State of Jammu and Kashmir which is engaged in the manufacture or production of any article or`
  line `thing specified in Part C of the Thirteenth Schedule.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 39, for “31st day of March, 2000” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2001).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 34, for “31st day of March, 2002” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2003).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 39 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 18, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 29, for “31st day of March, 2007” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_393_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_394:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-394
  sectionNo (394)
  orderNo 394
  title `Page 394`
  content obj_root_law_sections_394_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_394_footnotes
  sourcePage 394
obj_root_law_sections_394_content:
  string
  line 394
  line `( 5 ) The amount of deduction in the case of an industrial undertaking located in such industrially`
  line `backward districts as the Central Government may, having regard to the prescribed guidelines, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf as industrially backward district of ca tegory ‘A’`
  line `or an industrially backward district of category ‘B’ shall be,—`
  line `( i ) hundred per cent of the profits and gains derived from an industrial undertaking located in a`
  line `backward district of category ‘A’ for five assessment years beginning with the init ial assessment year`
  line `and thereafter, twenty-five per cent. (or thirty per cent. where the assessee is a company) of the profits`
  line `and gains of an industrial undertaking:`
  line `Provided that the total period of deduction shall not exceed ten consecutive assessment years or`
  line `where the assessee is a co-operative society, twelve consecutive assessment years:`
  line `Provided further that the industrial undertaking begins to manufacture or produce articles or things or`
  line `to operate its cold storage plant or plants at any time during the period beginning on the 1st day of`
  line `October, 1994 and ending on the 1 [31st day of March, 2004];`
  line `( ii ) hundred per cent. of the profits and gains derived from an industrial undertaking located in a`
  line `backward district of category ‘B’ for three assessment years beginning with the initial assessment year`
  line `and thereafter, twenty-five per cent (or thirty per cent where the assessee is a company) of the profits and`
  line `gains of an industrial undertaking:`
  line `Provided that the total period of deduction does not exceed eight consecutive assessment years (or where`
  line `the assessee is a co-operative society, twelve consecutive assessment years):`
  line `Provided further that the industrial undertaking begins to manufacture or produce articles or things or to`
  line `operate its cold storage plant or plants at any time during the period beginning on the 1st day of October,`
  line `1994 and ending on the 1 [31st day of March, 2004].`
  line `( 6 ) The amount of deduction in the case of the business of a ship shall be thirty per cent. of the profits`
  line `and gains derived from such ship for a period of ten consecutive assessment years including the initial`
  line `assessment year provided that the ship —`
  line `( i ) is owned by an Indian company and is wholly used for the purposes of the business carried on`
  line `by it;`
  line `( ii ) was not, previous to the date of its acquisition by the Indian company, owned or used in`
  line `Indian territorial waters by a person resident in India; and`
  line `( iii ) is brought into use by the Indian company at any time during the period beginning on the 1st`
  line `day of April, 1991 and ending on the 31st day of March, 1995.`
  line `( 7 ) The amount of deduction in the case of any hotel shall be —`
  line `( a ) fifty per cent. of the profits and gains derived from the business of such hotel for a period of`
  line `ten consecutive years beginning from the initial assessment year as is located in a hilly area or a rural`
  line `area or a place of pilgrimage or such other place as the Central Government may, having regard to the`
  line `need for development of infrastructure for tourism in any place and other relevant considerations,`
  line `specify by notification in the Official Gazette and such hotel starts functioning at any time during the`
  line `period beginning on the 1st day of April, 1990 and ending on the 31st day of March, 1994 or`
  line `beginning on the 1st day of April, 1997 and ending on the 31st day of March, 2001:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 34, for “31st day of March, 2002” (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_394_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_395:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-395
  sectionNo (395)
  orderNo 395
  title `Page 395`
  content obj_root_law_sections_395_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_395_footnotes
  sourcePage 395
obj_root_law_sections_395_content:
  string
  line 395
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall apply to a hotel located at a place within the`
  line `municipal jurisdiction (whether known as a municipality, municipal corporation, notified area`
  line `committee or a cantonment board or by any other name) of Calcutta, Chennai, Delhi or Mumbai,`
  line `which has started or starts functioning on or after the 1st day of April, 1997 and before the 31st day of`
  line `March, 2001:`
  line `Provided further that the said hotel is approved by the prescribed authority for the purpose of this`
  line `clause in accordance with the rules made under this Act and where the said hotel is approved by the`
  line `prescribed authority before the 31st day of March, 1992, shall be deemed to have been approved by`
  line `the prescribed authority for the purpose of this section in relation to the assessment year commencing`
  line `on the 1st day of April, 1991;`
  line `( b ) thirty per cent. of the profits and gains derived from the business of such hotel as is located in`
  line `any place other than those mentioned in sub-clause ( a ) for a period of ten consecutive years beginning`
  line `from the initial assessment year if such hotel has started or starts functioning at any time during the`
  line `period beginning on the 1st day of April, 1991 and ending on the 31st day of March, 1995 or`
  line `beginning on the 1st day of April, 1997 and ending on the 31st day of March, 2001:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall apply to a hotel located at a place within the`
  line `municipal jurisdiction (whether known as a municipality, municipal corporation, notified area`
  line `committee, town area committee or a cantonment board or by any other name) of Calcutta, Chennai,`
  line `Delhi or Mumbai, which has started or starts functioning on or after the 1st day of April, 1997 and`
  line `before the 31st day of March, 2001;`
  line `( c ) the deduction under clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) shall be available only if —`
  line `( i ) the business of the hotel is not formed by the splitting up, or the reconstruction, of a`
  line `business already in existence or by the transfer to a new business of a building previously used as`
  line `a hotel or of any machinery or plant previously used for any purpose;`
  line `( ii ) the business of the hotel is owned and carried on by a company registered in India with a`
  line `paid-up capital of not less than five hundred thousand rupees;`
  line `( iii ) the hotel is for the time being approved by the prescribed authority:`
  line `Provided that any hotel approved by the prescribed authority before the 1st day of April, 1999`
  line `shall be deemed to have been approved under this sub-section.`
  line `1 [( 7A ) The amount of deduction in the case of any multiplex theatre shall be —`
  line `( a ) fifty per cent of the profits and gains derived, from the business of building, owning and`
  line `operating a multiplex theatre, for a period of five consecutive years beginning from the initial`
  line `assessment year in any place:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall apply to a multiplex theatre located at a place`
  line `within the municipal jurisdiction (whether known as a municipality, municipal corporation, notified`
  line `area committee or a cantonment board or by any other name) of Chennai, Delhi, Mumbai or Kolkata;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_395_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_396:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-396
  sectionNo (396)
