  title `Page 396`
  content obj_root_law_sections_396_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_396_footnotes
  sourcePage 396
obj_root_law_sections_396_content:
  string
  line 396
  line `( b ) the deduction under clause ( a ) shall be allowable only if —`
  line `( i ) such multiplex theatre is constructed at any time during the period beginning on the 1st`
  line `day of April, 2002 and ending on the 31st day of March, 2005;`
  line `( ii ) the business of the multiplex theatre is not formed by the splitting up, or the`
  line `reconstruction, of a business already in existence or by the transfer to a new business of any`
  line `building or of any machinery or of plant previously used for any purpose;`
  line `( iii ) the assessee furnishes alongwith the return of income, the report of an audit in such form`
  line `and containing such particulars as may be prescribed and duly signed and verified by an`
  line `accountant, as defined in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288, certifying that the`
  line `deduction has been correctly claimed.`
  line `( 7B ) The amount of deduction in the case of any convention centre shall be —`
  line `( a ) fifty per cent of the profits and gains derived, by the assessee from the business of building,`
  line `owning and operating a convention centre, for a period of five consecutive years beginning from the`
  line `initial assessment year;`
  line `( b ) the deduction under clause ( a ) shall be allowable only if —`
  line `( i ) such convention centre is constructed at any time during the period beginning on the 1st`
  line `day of April, 2002 and ending on the 31st day of March, 2005;`
  line `( ii ) the business of the convention centre is not formed by the splitting up, or the`
  line `reconstruction, of a business already in existence or by the transfer to a new business of any`
  line `building or of any machinery or plant previously used for any purpose;`
  line `( iii ) the assessee furnishes alongwith the return of income, the report of an audit in such form`
  line `and containing such particulars as may be prescribed, and duly signed and verified by an`
  line `accountant, as defined in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288, certifying that the`
  line `deduction has been correctly claimed.]`
  line `( 8 ) The amount of deduction in the case of any company carrying on scientific research and`
  line `development shall be hundred per cent of the profits and gains of such business for a period of five`
  line `assessment years beginning from the initial assessment year if such company —`
  line `( a ) is registered in India;`
  line `( b ) has the main object of scientific and industrial research and development;`
  line `( c ) is for the time being approved by the prescribed authority at any time before the 1st day of`
  line `April, 1999.`
  line `1 [( 8A ) The amount of deduction in the case of any company carrying on scientific research and`
  line `development shall be hundred per cent of the profits and gains of such business for a period of ten`
  line `consecutive assessment years, beginning from the initial assessment year, if such company —`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 39 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_396_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_397:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-397
  sectionNo (397)
  orderNo 397
  title `Page 397`
  content obj_root_law_sections_397_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_397_footnotes
  sourcePage 397
obj_root_law_sections_397_content:
  string
  line 397
  line `( i ) is registered in India;`
  line `( ii ) has its main object the scientific and industrial research and development;`
  line `( iii ) is for the time being approved by the prescribed authority at any time after the 31st day of`
  line `March, 2000 but before the 1 [1st day of April, 2007];`
  line `( iv ) fulfils such other conditions as may be prescribed.]`
  line `2 [( 9 ) The amount of deduction to an undertaking shall be hundred per cent of the profits for a period`
  line `of seven consecutive assessment years, including the initial assessment year, if such undertaking fulfils`
  line `any of the following, namely: —`
  line `( i ) is located in North-Eastern Region and has begun or begins commercial production of mineral`
  line `oil before the 1st day of April, 1997;`
  line `( ii ) is located in any part of India and has begun or begins commercial production of mineral oil`
  line `on or after the 1st day of April, 1997 3 [but not later than the 31st day of March, 2017]:`
  line `4 [Provided that the provisions of this clause shall not apply to blocks licensed under a contract`
  line `awarded after the 31st day of March, 2011 under the New Exploration Licencing Policy announced`
  line `by the Government of India vide Resolution No. O-19018/22/95-ONG.DO.VL, dated the 10th`
  line `February, 1999 or in pursuance of any law for the time being in force or by the Central or a State`
  line `Government in any other manner;]`
  line `( iii ) is engaged in refining of mineral oil and begins such refining on or after the 1st day of`
  line `October, 1998 5 [but not later than the 31st day of March, 2012];`
  line `6 [( iv ) is engaged in commercial production of natural gas in blocks licensed under the VIII Round`
  line `of bidding for award of exploration contracts (hereafter referred to as “NELP -VII I”) under`
  line `the New Exploration Licencing Policy announced by the Government of India vide`
  line `Resolution No. O-19018/22/95-ONG.DO.VL, dated 10th February, 1999 and begins commercial`
  line `production of natural gas on or after the 1st day of April, 2009 5 [but not later than the 31st day of`
  line `March, 2017];`
  line `( v ) is engaged in commercial production of natural gas in blocks licensed under the IV Round of`
  line `bidding for award of exploration contracts for Coal Bed Methane blocks and begins commercial`
  line `production of natural gas on or after the 1st day of April, 2009 5 [but not later than the 31st day of`
  line `March, 2017].]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of claiming deduction under this sub-section, all blocks licensed`
  line `under a single contract, which has been awarded under the New Exploration Licencing Policy announced`
  line `by the Government of India vide Resolution No. O-19018/22/95-ONG.DO.VL, dated 10th February, 1999`
  line `or has been awarded in pursuance of any law for the time being in force or has been awarded by the`
  line `Central or a State Government in any other manner, shall be treated as a single “undertaking”. ]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 27, for “1st day of April, 2005” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006). Earlier substituted by Act 23 of 2004, s. 18`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2005), which was substituted by 32 of 2003, s. 39 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 37, for sub-section ( 9 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 43 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-2012).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
  line `6. Ins. by s. 37 ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
