obj_root_law_sections_398_content:
  string
  line 398
  line `1 [( 10 ) The amount of deduction in the case of an undertaking developing and building housing`
  line `projects approved before the 2 [31st day of March, 2008] by a local authority shall be hundred per cent of`
  line `the profits derived in the previous year relevant to any assessment year from such housing project if, —`
  line `( a ) such undertaking has commenced or commences development and construction of the`
  line `housing project on or after the 1st day of October, 1998 and completes such construction, —`
  line `( i ) in a case where a housing project has been approved by the local authority before the 1st`
  line `day of April, 2004, on or before the 31st day of March, 2008;`
  line `( ii ) in a case where a housing project has been, or, is approved by the local authority on or`
  line `after the 1st day of April, 2004 3 [but not later than the 31st day of March, 2005], within four years`
  line `from the end of the financial year in which the housing project is approved by the local authority;`
  line `3 [( iii ) in a case where a housing project has been approved by the local authority on or after`
  line `the 1st day of April, 2005, within five years from the end of the financial year in which the`
  line `housing project is approved by the local authority.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the approval in respect of the housing project is obtained more than`
  line `once, such housing project shall be deemed to have been approved on the date on which the`
  line `building plan of such housing project is first approved by the local authority;`
  line `( ii ) the date of completion of construction of the housing project shall be taken to be the`
  line `date on which the completion certificate in respect of such housing project is issued by the`
  line `local authority;`
  line `( b ) the project is on the size of a plot of land which has a minimum area of one acre:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) shall apply to a housing project carried`
  line `out in accordance with a scheme framed by the Central Government or a State Government for`
  line `reconstruction or redevelopment of existing buildings in areas declared to be slum areas under any`
  line `law for the time being in force and such scheme is notified by the Board in this behalf;`
  line `( c ) the residential unit has a maximum built-up area of one thousand square feet where such`
  line `residential unit is situated within the city of Delhi or Mumbai or within twenty-five kilometres from`
  line `the municipal limits of these cities and one thousand and five hundred square feet at 4 [any other`
  line place;]
  line `( d ) the built-up area of the shops and other commercial establishments included in the housing`
  line `project does not exceed 5 [three per cent.] of the aggregate built-up area of the housing project or 6 [five`
  line `thousand square feet], whichever is higher;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 18, for sub-section ( 10 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2005). As later on amended by Act 10 of 2000, s. 29`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 37, for “31st day of March, 2007” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2009).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 37, for “any other place; and” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2010).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 27, for “five per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2010).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 27, ibid., for “two thousand square feet, whichever is less” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2010).`
