  title `Page 400`
  content obj_root_law_sections_400_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_400_footnotes
  sourcePage 400
obj_root_law_sections_400_content:
  string
  line 400
  line `( ii ) the hospital has at least one hundred beds for patients;`
  line `( iii ) the construction of the hospital is in accordance with the regulations, for the time being in`
  line `force, of the local authority; and`
  line `( iv ) the assessee furnishes along with the return of income, the report of audit in such form and`
  line `containing such particulars as may be prescribed, and duly signed and verified by an accountant, as`
  line `defined in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288, certifying that the deduction has`
  line `been correctly claimed.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, a hospital shall be deemed to have been`
  line `constructed on the date on which a completion certificate in respect of such construction is issued by the`
  line `concerned local authority.]`
  line `1 [( 11C ) The amount of deduction in the case of an undertaking deriving profits from the business of`
  line `operating and maintaining a hospital located anywhere in India, other than the excluded area, shall be`
  line `hundred per cent of the profits and gains derived from such business for a period of five consecutive`
  line `assessment years, beginning with the initial assessment year, if —`
  line `( i ) the hospital is constructed and has started or starts functioning at any time during the period`
  line `beginning on the 1st day of April, 2008 and ending on the 31st day of March, 2013;`
  line `( ii ) the hospital has at least one hundred beds for patients;`
  line `( iii ) the construction of the hospital is in accordance with the regulations or bye-laws of the local`
  line `authority; and`
  line `( iv ) the assessee furnishes along with the return of income, a report of audit in such form and`
  line `containing such particulars, as may be prescribed, and duly signed and verified by an accountant, as`
  line `defined in the Explanation to sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288, certifying that the deduction has been`
  line `correctly claimed.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section —`
  line `( a ) a hospital shall be deemed to have been constructed on the date on which a completion`
  line `certificate in respect of such construction is issued by the local authority concerned;`
  line `( b ) “initial assessment year” means the assessment year relevant to the previous year in which the`
  line `business of the hospital starts functioning;`
  line `( c ) “excluded area” shall mean an area comprising—`
  line `( i ) Greater Mumbai urban agglomeration;`
  line `( ii ) Delhi urban agglomeration;`
  line `( iii ) Kolkata urban agglomeration;`
  line `( iv ) Chennai urban agglomeration;`
  line `( v ) Hyderabad urban agglomeration;`
  line `( vi ) Bangalore urban agglomeration;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_400_footnotes:
