  line
obj_root_law_sections_403:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-403
  sectionNo (403)
  orderNo 403
  title `Page 403`
  content obj_root_law_sections_403_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_403_footnotes
  sourcePage 403
obj_root_law_sections_403_content:
  string
  line 403
  line `1 [ 80-IBA. Deductions in respect of profits and gains from housing projects. — ( 1 ) Where the gross`
  line `total income of an assessee includes any profits and gains derived from the business of developing and`
  line `building housing projects, there shall, subject to the provisions of this section, be allowed, a deduction of`
  line `an amount equal to hundred per cent of the profits and gains derived from such business.`
  line `( 2 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), a housing project shall be a project which fulfils the following`
  line `conditions, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the project is approved by the competent authority after the 1st day of June, 2016, but on or`
  line `before the 31st day of March, 2 [2020];`
  line `( b ) the project is completed within a period of 3 [ five years] from the date of approval by the`
  line `competent authority:`
  line `Provided that, —`
  line `( i ) where the approval in respect of a housing project is obtained more than once, the project`
  line `shall be deemed to have been approved on the date on which the building plan of such housing`
  line `project was first approved by the competent authority; and`
  line `( ii ) the project shall be deemed to have been completed when a certificate of completion of`
  line `project as a whole is obtained in writing from the competent authority;`
  line `( c ) the 4 [carpet area] of the shops and other commercial establishments included in the housing`
  line `project does not exceed three per cent. of the aggregate 4 [carpet area];`
  line `( d ) the project is on a plot of land measuring not less than —`
  line `( i ) one thousand square metres, where the project is located within the cities of Chennai,`
  line `Delhi, Kolkata or Mumbai 5 ***; or`
  line `( ii ) two thousand square metres, where the project is located in any other place;`
  line `( e ) the project is the only housing project on the plot of land as specified in clause ( d );`
  line `( f ) the 4 [carpet area] of the residential unit comprised in the housing project does not exceed —`
  line `( i ) thirty square metres, where the project is located within the cities of Chennai, Delhi,`
  line `Kolkata or Mumbai 5 ***; or`
  line `( ii ) sixty square metres, where the project is located in any other place;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 44 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 7, for “2019” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2020).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 37, for “three years” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2018).`
  line `4. Subs. by 37, ibid., for “built - up area” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2018).`
  line `5. The words “or within the distance, measured aerially, of twenty - five kilometres from the municipal limits of these cities”`
  line `omitted by s. 37, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_403_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_404:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-404
  sectionNo (404)
  orderNo 404
  title `Page 404`
  content obj_root_law_sections_404_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_404_footnotes
  sourcePage 404
obj_root_law_sections_404_content:
  string
  line 404
  line `( g ) where a residential unit in the housing project is allotted to an individual, no other residential`
  line `unit in the housing project shall be allotted to the individual or the spouse or the minor children of`
  line `such individual;`
  line `( h ) the project utilises —`
  line `( i ) not less than ninety per cent of the floor area ratio permissible in respect of the plot of land`
  line `under the rules to be made by the Central Government or the State Government or the local`
  line `authority, as the case may be, where the project is located within the cities of Chennai, Delhi,`
  line `Kolkata or Mumbai 1 ***, or`
  line `( ii ) not less than eighty per cent of such floor area ratio where such project is located in any`
  line `place other than the place referred to in sub-clause ( i ); and`
  line `( i ) the assessee maintains separate books of account in respect of the housing project.`
  line `( 3 ) Nothing contained in this section shall apply to any assessee who executes the housing project as`
  line `a works-contract awarded by any person (including the Central Government or the State Government).`
  line `( 4 ) Where the housing project is not completed within the period specified under clause ( b ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) and in respect of which a deduction has been claimed and allowed under this section, the`
  line `total amount of deduction so claimed and allowed in one or more previous years, shall be deemed to be`
  line `the income of the assessee chargeable under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession” of the`
  line `previous year in which the period for completion so expires.`
  line `( 5 ) Where any amount of profits and gains derived from the business of developing and building`
  line `housing projects is claimed and allowed under this section for any assessment year, deduction to the`
  line `extent of such profit and gains shall not be allowed under any other provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 6 ) For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `2 [( a ) “carpet area” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause ( k ) of section 2 of the`
  line `Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act, 2016 (16 of 2016).]`
  line `( b ) “competent authority” means the authority empowered to approve the building plan by or`
  line `under any law for the time being in force;`
  line `( c ) “floor area ratio” means the quotient obtained by dividing the total covered area of plinth area`
  line `on all the floors by the area of the plot of land;`
  line `( d ) “housing project” mea ns a project consisting predominantly of residential units with such`
  line `other facilities and amenities as the competent authority may approve subject to the provisions of this`
  line section;
  line `( e ) “residential unit” means an independent housing unit with separate fac ilities for living,`
  line `cooking and sanitary requirements, distinctly separated from other residential units within the`
  line `building, which is directly accessible from an outer door or through an interior door in a shared`
  line `hallway and not by walking through the living space of another household.]`
  line `1. The words “or within the distance, measured aerially, of twenty -five kilometres from the municipal limits of these cities”`
  line `omitted by Act 7 of 2017, s. 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 37, ibid., for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_404_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_405:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-405
