  title `Page 405`
  content obj_root_law_sections_405_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_405_footnotes
  sourcePage 405
obj_root_law_sections_405_content:
  string
  line 405
  line `1 [ 80-IC. Special provisions in respect of certain undertakings or enterprises in certain special`
  line `category States. — ( 1 ) Where the gross total income of an assessee includes any profits and gains derived`
  line `by an undertaking or an enterprise from any business referred to in sub-section ( 2 ), there shall, in`
  line `accordance with and subject to the provisions of this section, be allowed, in computing the total income of`
  line `the assessee, a deduction from such profits and gains, as specified in sub-section ( 3 ).`
  line `( 2 ) This section applies to any undertaking or enterprise, —`
  line `( a ) which has begun or begins to manufacture or produce any article or thing, not being any`
  line `article or thing specified in the Thirteenth Schedule, or which manufactures or produces any article or`
  line `thing, not being any article or thing specified in the Thirteenth Schedule and undertakes substantial`
  line `expansion during the period beginning —`
  line `( i ) on the 23rd day of December, 2002 and ending before the 2 [1st day of April, 2007], in`
  line `any Export Processing Zone or Integrated Infrastructure Development Centre or Industrial`
  line `Growth Centre or Industrial Estate or Industrial Park or Software Technology Park or Industrial`
  line `Area or Theme Park, as notified by the Board in accordance with the scheme framed and`
  line `notified by the Central Government in this regard, in the State of Sikkim; or`
  line `( ii ) on the 7th day of January, 2003 and ending before the 1st day of April, 2012, in any`
  line `Export Processing Zone or Integrated Infrastructure Development Centre or Industrial Growth`
  line `Centre or Industrial Estate or Industrial Park or Software Technology Park or Industrial Area or`
  line `Theme Park, as notified by the Board in accordance with the scheme framed and notified by the`
  line `Central Government in this regard, in the State of Himachal Pradesh or the State of Uttaranchal;`
  line or
  line `( iii ) on the 24th day of December, 1997 and ending before the 1st day of April, 2007, in any`
  line `Export Processing Zone or Integrated Infrastructure Development Centre or Industrial Growth`
  line `Centre or Industrial Estate or Industrial Park or Software Technology Park or Industrial Area or`
  line `Theme Park, as notified by the Board in accordance with the scheme framed and notified by the`
  line `Central Government in this regard, in any of the North-Eastern States;`
  line `( b ) which has begun or begins to manufacture or produce any article or thing, specified in the`
  line `Fourteenth Schedule or commences any operation specified in that Schedule, or which manufactures`
  line `or produces any article or thing, specified in the Fourteenth Schedule or commences any operation`
  line `specified in that Schedule and undertakes substantial expansion during the period beginning —`
  line `( i ) on the 23rd day of December, 2002 and ending before the 2 [1st day of April, 2007], in the`
  line `State of Sikkim; or`
  line `( ii ) on the 7th day of January, 2003 and ending before the 1st day of April, 2012, in the State`
  line `of Himachal Pradesh or the State of Uttaranchal; or`
  line `( iii ) on the 24th day of December, 1997 and ending before the 1st day of April, 2007, in any`
  line `of the North-Eastern States.`
  line `( 3 ) The deduction referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be —`
  line `( i ) in the case of any undertaking or enterprise referred to in sub-clauses ( i ) and ( iii ) of clause ( a )`
  line `or sub-clauses ( i ) and ( iii ) of clause ( b ), of sub-section ( 2 ), one hundred per cent. of such profits and`
  line `gains for ten assessment years commencing with the initial assessment year;`
  line `( ii ) in the case of any undertaking or enterprise referred to in sub-clause ( ii ) of clause ( a ) or`
  line `sub-clause ( ii ) of clause ( b ), of sub-section ( 2 ), one hundred per cent of such profits and gains for five`
  line `assessment years commencing with the initial assessment year and thereafter, twenty-five per cent.`
  line `(or thirty per cent. where the assessee is a company) of the profits and gains.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 30, for “1st day of April, 2012” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_405_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_406:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-406
  sectionNo (406)
  orderNo 406
  title `Page 406`
  content obj_root_law_sections_406_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_406_footnotes
  sourcePage 406
obj_root_law_sections_406_content:
  string
  line 406
  line `( 4 ) This section applies to any undertaking or enterprise which fulfils all the following conditions,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( i ) it is not formed by splitting up, or the reconstruction, of a business already in existence:`
  line `Provided that this condition shall not apply in respect of an undertaking which is formed as a`
  line `result of the re-establishment, reconstruction or revival by the assessee of the business of any such`
  line `undertaking as is referred to in section 33B, in the circumstances and within the period specified in`
  line `that section;`
  line `( ii ) it is not formed by the transfer to a new business of machinery or plant previously used for`
  line `any purpose.`
  line `Explanation. — The provisions of Explanations 1 and 2 to sub-section ( 3 ) of sectopm 80-IA shall`
  line `apply for the purposes of clause ( ii ) of this sub-section as they apply for the purposes of clause ( ii ) of that`
  line sub-section.
  line `( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, in computing the total`
  line `income of the assessee, no deduction shall be allowed under any other section contained in Chapter VIA`
  line `or in section 10A or section 10B, in relation to the profits and gains of the undertaking or enterprise.`
  line `( 6 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, no deduction shall be allowed to any undertaking`
  line `or enterprise under this section, where the total period of deduction inclusive of the period of deduction`
  line `under this section, or under the second proviso to sub-section ( 4 ) of section 80-IB or under section 10C,`
  line `as the case may be, exceeds ten assessment years.`
  line `( 7 ) The provisions contained in sub-section ( 5 ) and sub-sections ( 7 ) to ( 12 ) of section 80-IA shall, so`
  line `far as may be, apply to the eligible undertaking or enterprise under this section.`
  line `( 8 ) For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “Industrial Area” means such areas, which the Board, may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify in accordance with the scheme framed and notified by the Central Government;`
  line `( ii ) “Industrial Estate” means such estates, which the Board, may, by notifi cation in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify in accordance with the scheme framed and notified by the Central Government;`
  line `( iii ) “Industrial Growth Centre” means such centres, which the Board, may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, specify in accordance with the scheme framed and notified by the Central`
  line Government;
  line `( iv ) “Industrial Park” means such parks, which the Board, may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify in accordance with the scheme framed and notified by the Central Government;`
  line `( v ) “Initial assessment year” means the assessment year relevant to the previous year in which`
  line `the undertaking or the enterprise begins to manufacture or produce articles or things, or commences`
  line `operation or completes substantial expansion;`
  line `( vi ) “Integrated Infrastructure Development Centre” means such centres, which the Board, may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in accordance with the scheme framed and notified by`
  line `the Central Government;`
  line `( vii ) “North - Eastern States” means the States of Arunac hal Pradesh, Assam, Manipur,`
  line `Meghalaya, Mizoram, Nagaland and Tripura;`
  line `( viii ) “Software Technology Park” means any park set up in accordance with the Software`
  line `Technology Park Scheme notified by the Government of India in the Ministry of Commerce and`
  line Industry;
  line `( ix ) “Substantial expansion” means increase in the investment in the plant and machinery by at`
  line `least fifty per cent of the book value of plant and machinery (before taking depreciation in any year),`
  line `as on the first day of the previous year in which the substantial expansion is undertaken;`
  line `( x ) “Theme Park” means such parks, which the Board, may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify in accordance with the scheme framed and notified by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_406_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_407:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-407
  sectionNo (407)
  orderNo 407
  title `Page 407`
  content obj_root_law_sections_407_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_407_footnotes
  sourcePage 407
obj_root_law_sections_407_content:
  string
  line 407
  line `1 [ 80-ID. Deduction in respect of profits and gains from business of hotels and convention`
  line `centres in specified area. — ( 1 ) Where the gross total income of an assessee includes any profits and`
  line `gains derived by an undertaking from any business referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) (such business being`
  line `hereinafter referred to as the eligible business), there shall, in accordance with and subject to the`
  line `provisions of this section, be allowed, in computing the total income of the assessee, a deduction of an`
  line `amount equal to hundred per cent of the profits and gains derived from such business for five consecutive`
  line `assessment years beginning from the initial assessment year.`
  line `( 2 ) This section applies to any undertaking, —`
  line `( i ) engaged in the business of hotel located in the specified area, if such hotel is constructed and`
  line `has started or starts functioning at any time during the period beginning on the 1st day of April, 2007`
  line `and ending on 2 [the 31st day of July, 2010]; or`
  line `( ii ) engaged in the business of building, owning and operating a convention centre, located in the`
  line `specified area, if such convention centre is constructed at any time during the period beginning on the`
  line `1st day of April, 2007 and ending on 2 [the 31st day of July, 2010];`
  line `3 [( iii ) engaged in the business of hotel located in the specified district having a World Heritage`
  line `Site, if such hotel is constructed and has started or starts functioning at any time during the period`
  line `beginning on the 1st day of April, 2008 and ending on the 31st day of March, 2013.]`
  line `( 3 ) The deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be available only if —`
  line `( i ) the eligible business is not formed by the splitting up, or the reconstruction, of a business`
  line `already in existence;`
  line `( ii ) the eligible business is not formed by the transfer to a new business of a building previously`
  line `used as a hotel or a convention centre, as the case may be;`
  line `( iii ) the eligible business is not formed by the transfer to a new business of machinery or plant`
  line `previously used for any purpose.`
  line `Explanation. — The provisions of Explanations 1 and 2 to sub-section ( 3 ) of section 80-IA shall apply`
  line `for the purposes of clause (iii) of this sub-section as they apply for the purposes of clause ( ii ) of that`
  line sub-section;
  line `( iv ) the assessee furnishes along with the return of income, the report of an audit in such form and`
  line `containing such particulars as may be prescribed, and duly signed and verified by an accountant, as`
  line `defined in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288, certifying that the deduction has`
  line `been correctly claimed.`
  line `( 4 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, in computing the total`
  line `income of the assessee, no deduction shall be allowed under any other section contained in Chapter VIA`
  line `or section 10AA, in relation to the profits and gains of the undertaking.`
  line `( 5 ) The provisions contained in sub-section ( 5 ) and sub-sections ( 8 ) to ( 11 ) of section 80-IA shall, so`
  line `far as may be, apply to the eligible business under this section.`
  line `( 6 ) For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “convention centre” means a building of a prescribed area comprising of convention halls to`
  line `be used for the purpose of holding conferences and seminars, being of such size and number and`
  line `having such other facilities and amenities, as may be prescribed;`
  line `( b ) “hotel” means a hotel of two -star, three-star or four-star category as classified by the Central`
  line Government;
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 28, for “the 31st day of March, 2010” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2011).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_407_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_408:
