obj_root_law_sections_408_content:
  string
  line 408
  line `( c ) “ initial assessment year”—`
  line `( i ) in the case of a hotel, means the assessment year relevant to the previous year in which`
  line `the business of the hotel starts functioning;`
  line `( ii ) in the case of a convention centre, means the assessment year relevant to the previous`
  line `year in which the convention centre starts operating on a commercial basis;`
  line `( d ) “specified area” means the Nati onal Capital Territory of Delhi and the districts of Faridabad,`
  line `Gurgaon, Gautam Budh Nagar and Ghaziabad;]`
  line `1 [( e ) “specified district having a World Heritage Site” means districts, specified in column (2) of`
  line `the Table below, of the States, specified in the corresponding entry in column (3) of the said Table:`
  line TABLE
  line `S.No. Name of district Name of State`
  line `( 1 ) ( 2 ) ( 3 )`
  line `1. Agra Uttar Pradesh`
  line `2. Jalgaon Maharashtra`
  line `3. Aurangabad Maharashtra`
  line `4. Kancheepuram Tamil Nadu`
  line `5. Puri Orissa`
  line `6. Bharatpur Rajasthan`
  line `7. Chhatarpur Madhya Pradesh`
  line `8. Thanjavur Tamil Nadu`
  line `9. Bellary Karnataka`
  line `10. South 24 Parganas West Bengal`
  line `(excluding areas falling within the Kolkata`
  line `urban agglomeration on the basis of the 2001`
  line `census)`
  line `11. Chamoli Uttarakhand`
  line `12. Raisen Madhya Pradesh`
  line `13. Gaya Bihar`
  line `14. Bhopal Madhya Pradesh`
  line `15. Panchmahal Gujarat`
  line `16. Kamrup Assam`
  line `17. Goalpara Assam`
  line `18. Nagaon Assam`
  line `19. North Goa Goa`
  line `20. South Goa Goa`
  line `21. Darjeeling West Bengal`
  line `22. Nilgiri Tamil Nadu.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_408_footnotes:
