  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_409_footnotes
  sourcePage 409
obj_root_law_sections_409_content:
  string
  line 409
  line `1 [ 80-IE. Special provisions in respect of certain undertakings in North-Eastern States. — ( 1 )`
  line `Where the gross total income of an assessee includes any profits and gains derived by an undertaking, to`
  line `which this section applies, from any business referred to in sub-section ( 2 ), there shall be allowed, in`
  line `computing the total income of the assessee, a deduction of an amount equal to hundred per cent of the`
  line `profits and gains derived from such business for ten consecutive assessment years commencing with the`
  line `initial assessment year.`
  line `( 2 ) This section applies to any undertaking which has, during the period beginning on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2007 and ending before the 1st day of April, 2017, begun or begins, in any of the North-Eastern`
  line `States, —`
  line `( i ) to manufacture or produce any eligible article or thing;`
  line `( ii ) to undertake substantial expansion to manufacture or produce any eligible article or thing;`
  line `( iii ) to carry on any eligible business.`
  line `( 3 ) This section applies to any undertaking which fulfils all the following conditions, namely: —`
  line `( i ) it is not formed by splitting up, or the reconstruction, of a business already in existence:`
  line `Provided that this condition shall not apply in respect of an undertaking which is formed as a`
  line `result of the re-establishment, reconstruction or revival by the assessee of the business of any such`
  line `undertaking as referred to in section 33B, in the circumstances and within the period specified in the`
  line `said section;`
  line `( ii ) it is not formed by the transfer to a new business of machinery or plant previously used for`
  line `any purpose.`
  line `Explanation. — The provisions of Explanations 1 and 2 to sub-section ( 3 ) of section 80-IA shall apply`
  line `for the purposes of clause ( ii ) of this sub-section as they apply for the purposes of clause ( ii ) of that`
  line sub-section.
  line `( 4 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, in computing the total`
  line `income of the assessee, no deduction shall be allowed under any other section contained in Chapter VIA`
  line `or in section 10A or section 10AA or section 10B or section 10BA, in relation to the profits and gains of`
  line `the undertaking.`
  line `( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, no deduction shall be allowed to any undertaking`
  line `under this section, where the total period of deduction inclusive of the period of deduction under this`
  line `section, or under section 80-IC or under the second proviso to sub-section ( 4 ) of section 80-IB or`
  line `under section 10C, as the case may be, exceeds ten assessment years.`
  line `( 6 ) The provisions contained in sub-section ( 5 ) and sub-sections ( 7 ) to ( 12 ) of section 80-IA shall, so`
  line `far as may be, apply to the eligible undertaking under this section.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_409_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_410:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-410
