  title `Page 410`
  content obj_root_law_sections_410_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_410_footnotes
  sourcePage 410
obj_root_law_sections_410_content:
  string
  line 410
  line `( 7 ) For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “initial assessment year” means the assessment year relevant to the previous year in which the`
  line `undertaking begins to manufacture or produce articles or things, or completes substantial expansion;`
  line `( ii ) “North - Eastern States” means the States of Arunachal Pradesh, Assam, Manipur, Meghalaya,`
  line `Mizoram, Nagaland, Sikkim and Tripura;`
  line `( iii ) “substantial expansion” means incre ase in the investment in the plant and machinery by at`
  line `least twenty-five per cent of the book value of plant and machinery (before taking depreciation in any`
  line `year), as on the first day of the previous year in which the substantial expansion is undertaken;`
  line `( iv ) “eligible article or thing” means the article or thing other than the following:—`
  line `( a ) goods falling under Chapter 24 of the First Schedule to the Central Excise Tariff`
  line `Act, 1985 (5 of 1986), which pertains to tobacco and manufactured tobacco substitutes;`
  line `( b ) pan masala as covered under Chapter 21 of the First Schedule to the Central Excise Tariff`
  line `Act, 1985 (5 of 1986);`
  line `( c ) plastic carry bags of less than 20 microns as specified by the Ministry of Environment`
  line `and Forests vide Notification No. S.O. 705(E), dated the 2nd September, 1999 and S.O. 698(E),`
  line `dated the 17th June, 2003; and`
  line `( d ) goods falling under Chapter 27 of the First Schedule to the Central Excise Tariff`
  line `Act, 1985 (5 of 1986), produced by petroleum oil or gas refineries;`
  line `( v ) “eligible business” means the business of,—`
  line `( a ) hotel (not below two star category);`
  line `( b ) adventure and leisure sports including ropeways;`
  line `( c ) providing medical and health services in the nature of nursing home with a minimum`
  line `capacity of 25 beds;`
  line `( d ) running an old-age home;`
  line `( e ) operating vocational training institute for hotel management, catering and food craft,`
  line `entrepreneurship development, nursing and para-medical, civil aviation related training, fashion`
  line `designing and industrial training;`
  line `( f ) running information technology related training centre;`
  line `( g ) manufacturing of information technology hardware; and`
  line `( h ) bio-technology.]`
  line `80J. [ Deduction in respect of profits and gains from newly established industrial undertakings`
  line `or ships or hotel business in certain cases ]. — Omitted by the Finance ( No. 2) Act, 1996 (33 of 1996),`
  line `s. 29 ( w.r.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_410_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_411:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-411
  sectionNo (411)
  orderNo 411
  title `Page 411`
  content obj_root_law_sections_411_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_411_footnotes
  sourcePage 411
obj_root_law_sections_411_content:
  string
  line 411
  line `80JJ. [ Deduction in respect of profits and gains from business of poultry farming ]. — Omitted by`
  line `the Finance Act, 1997 (26 of 1997), s. 26 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `1 [ 80JJA. Deduction in respect of profits and gains from business of collecting and processing of`
  line `bio-degradable waste. — Where the gross total income of an assessee includes any profits and gains`
  line `derived from the business of collecting and processing or treating of bio-degradable waste for generating`
  line `power 2 [or producing bio-fertilizers, bio-pesticides or other biological agents or for producing bio-gas or]`
  line `making pellets or briquettes for fuel or organic manure, there shall be allowed, in computing the total`
  line `income of the assessee, 3 [a deduction of an amount equal to the whole of such profits and gains for a`
  line `period of five consecutive assessment years beginning with the assessment year relevant to the previous`
  line `year in which such business commences].`
  line `4 [ 80JJAA. Deduction in respect of employment of new employees. — ( 1 ) Where the gross total`
  line `income of an assessee to whom section 44AB applies, includes any profits and gains derived from`
  line `business, there shall, subject to the conditions specified in sub-section ( 2 ), be allowed a deduction of an`
  line `amount equal to thirty per cent. of additional employee cost incurred in the course of such business in the`
  line `previous year, for three assessment years including the assessment year relevant to the previous year in`
  line `which such employment is provided.`
  line `( 2 ) No deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be allowed, —`
  line `( a ) if the business is formed by splitting up, or the reconstruction, of an existing business:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall apply in respect of a business which is formed`
  line `as a result of re-establishment, reconstruction or revival by the assessee of the business in the`
  line `circumstances and within the period specified in section 33B;`
  line `( b ) if the business is acquired by the assessee by way of transfer from any other person or as a`
  line `result of any business reorganisation;`
  line `( c ) unless the assessee furnishes alongwith the return of income the report of the accountant, as`
  line `defined in the Explanation to section 288 giving such particulars in the report as may be prescribed.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “additional employee cost” means total emoluments paid o r payable to additional employees`
  line `employed during the previous year:`
  line `Provided that in the case of an existing business, the additional employee cost shall be nil, if —`
  line `( a ) there is no increase in the number of employees from the total number of employees`
  line `employed as on the last day of the preceding year;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999). Earlier section 80JJA was inserted by Act 21 of 1979, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-`
  line `1980) and later omitted by Act 11 of 1983, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-1984).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 51, for “, producing bio - gas” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2000).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 51, ibid., for “a deduction from such profits and gains of an amount equal to the whole of such income, or five`
  line `lakh rupees, whichever is less” (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 45, for section 80JJAA (w.e.f. 1-4-2017). Earlier section 80JJAA was inserted by Act 21 of`
  line `1998, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_411_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_412:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-412
  sectionNo (412)
  orderNo 412
  title `Page 412`
  content obj_root_law_sections_412_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_412_footnotes
  sourcePage 412
obj_root_law_sections_412_content:
  string
  line 412
  line `( b ) emoluments are paid otherwise than by an account payee cheque or account payee bank`
  line `draft or by use of electronic clearing system through a bank account:`
  line `Provided further that in the first year of a new business, emoluments paid or payable to`
  line `employees employed during that previous year shall be deemed to be the additional employee`
  line cost;
  line `( ii ) “additional employee” means an employee who has been employed during the previous year`
  line `and whose employment has the effect of increasing the total number of employees employed by the`
  line `employer as on the last day of the preceding year, but does not include, —`
  line `( a ) an employee whose total emoluments are more than twenty-five thousand rupees per`
  line `month; or`
  line `( b ) an employee for whom the entire contribution is paid by the Government under the`
  line `Employees’ Pension Scheme notified in accordance with the provisions of the Employees’`
  line `Provident Funds and Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1952 (19 of 1952); or`
  line `( c ) an employee employed for a period of less than two hundred and forty days during the`
  line `previous year; or`
  line `( d ) an employee who does not participate in the recognised provident fund:`
  line `1 [Provided that in the case of an assessee who is engaged in the business of manufacturing of`
  line `apparel, 2 [or footwear or leather products] the provisions of sub-clause ( c ) shall have effect as if`
  line `for the words “two hundred and forty days”, the words “one hundred and fifty days” had been`
  line `substituted:]`
  line `1 [Provided further that where an employee is employed during the previous year for a period`
  line `of less than two hundred and forty days or one hundred and fifty days, as the case may be, but is`
  line `employed for a period of two hundred and forty days or one hundred and fifty days, as the case`
  line `may be, in the immediately succeeding year, he shall be deemed to have been employed in the`
  line `succeeding year and the provisions of this section shall apply accordingly;]`
  line `( iii ) “emoluments” means any sum paid or payable to an employee in lieu of his employment by`
  line `whatever name called, but does not include —`
  line `( a ) any contribution paid or payable by the employer to any pension fund or provident fund`
  line `or any other fund for the benefit of the employee under any law for the time being in force; and`
  line `( b ) any lump-sum payment paid or payable to an employee at the time of termination of his`
  line `service or superannuation or voluntary retirement, such as gratuity, severance pay, leave`
  line `encashment, voluntary retrenchment benefits, commutation of pension and the like.`
  line `( 3 ) The provisions of this section, as they stood immediately prior to their amendment by the Finance`
  line `Act, 2016, shall apply to an assessee eligible to claim any deduction for any assessment year commencing`
  line `on or before the 1st day of April, 2016.]`
  line `80K. [ Deduction in respect of dividends attributable to profits and gains from new industrial`
  line `undertakings or ships or hotel business ]. — Omitted by the Finance Act, 1986 (23 of 1986), s. 19`
  line `( w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 47 of 2016, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
