  sourcePage 413
obj_root_law_sections_413_content:
  string
  line 413
  line `80L. [ Deductions in respect of interest on certain securities, dividends, etc ]. — Omitted by the`
  line `Finance Act, 2005 (18 of 2005), s. 28 ( w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `1 [ 80LA. Deductions in respect of certain incomes of Offshore Banking Units and International`
  line `Financial Services Centre. — ( 1 ) Where the gross total income of an assessee, —`
  line `( i ) being a scheduled bank, or, any bank incorporated by or under the laws of a country outside`
  line `India; and having an Offshore Banking Unit in a Special Economic Zone; or`
  line `( ii ) being a Unit of an International Financial Services Centre,`
  line `includes any income referred to in sub-section ( 2 ), there shall be allowed, in accordance with and subject`
  line `to the provisions of this section, a deduction from such income, of an amount equal to —`
  line `( a ) one hundred per cent of such income for five consecutive assessment years beginning with`
  line `the assessment year relevant to the previous year in which the permission, under clause ( a ) of sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ) of section 23 of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949) or permission or`
  line `registration under the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992) or any other`
  line `relevant law was obtained, and thereafter;`
  line `( b ) fifty per cent. of such income for five consecutive assessment years.`
  line `( 2 ) The income referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be the income —`
  line `( a ) from an Offshore Banking Unit in a Special Economic Zone; or`
  line `( b ) from the business referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 6 of the Banking Regulation`
  line `Act, 1949 (10 of 1949) with an undertaking located in a Special Economic Zone or any other`
  line `undertaking which develops, develops and operates or develops, operates and maintains a Special`
  line `Economic Zone; or`
  line `( c ) from any Unit of the International Financial Services Centre from its business for which it has`
  line `been approved for setting up in such a Centre in a Special Economic Zone.`
  line `( 3 ) No deduction under this section shall be allowed unless the assessee furnishes along with the`
  line `return of income, —`
  line `( i ) the report, in the form specified by the Central Board of Direct Taxes under clause ( i ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 80LA, as it stood immediately before its substitution by this section, of an`
  line `accountant as defined in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288, certifying that the`
  line `deduction has been correctly claimed in accordance with the provisions of this section; and`
  line `( ii ) a copy of the permission obtained under clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 23 of the`
  line `Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949).`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2005, s. 27 and the Second Schedule, for section 80LA (w.e.f. 10-2-2006). Earlier inserted by 32 of`
  line `2003, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
