obj_root_law_sections_415_content:
  string
  line 415
  line `( ii ) thirty per cent. for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2002;`
  line `( iii ) twenty per cent. for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2003;`
  line `( iv ) ten per cent. for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2004,`
  line `of the income so received in, or brought into, India, in computing the total income of the assessee and no`
  line `deduction shall be allowed in respect of the assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2005 and`
  line `any subsequent assessment year]]:`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `2 [ 3 [Provided] that such income is received in India within a period of six months from the end of the`
  line `previous year, or 4 [within such further period as the competent authority may allow in this behalf]:]`
  line `5 [Provided further that no deduction under this section shall be allowed unless the assessee furnishes a`
  line `certificate, in the prescribed form, along with the return of income, certifying that the deduction has been`
  line `correctly claimed in accordance with the provisions of this section.]`
  line `6 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “convertible foreign exchange” means foreign exchange which is for the time being treated by`
  line `the Reserve Bank of India as convertible foreign exchange for the purposes of the law for the time`
  line `being in force for regulating payments and dealings in foreign exchange;`
  line `2 [( ii ) “foreign enterprise” means a person who is a non -resident;]]`
  line `7 [( iii ) services rendered or agreed to be rendered outside India shall include services rendered`
  line `from India but shall not include services rendered in India;]`
  line `8 [( iv ) “competent authority” means the Reserv e Bank of India or such other authority as is`
  line `authorised under any law for the time being in force for regulating payments and dealings in foreign`
  line exchange.]
  line `9 * * * * *`
  line `[ 80P. Deduction in respect of income of co-operative societies. — ( 1 ) Where, in the case of an`
  line `assessee being a co-operative society, the gross total income includes any income referred to in sub-`
  line `section ( 2 ), there shall be deducted, in accordance with and subject to the provisions of this section, the`
  line `sums specified in sub-section ( 2 ), in computing the total income of the assessee.`
  line `( 2 ) The sums referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be the following, namely: —`
  line `( a ) in the case of a co-operative society engaged in —`
  line `1. The provisos omitted by Act 49 of 1991, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 34, for “Provided also” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1992).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 53, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).earlier amended by Act 20 of 1974, s. 9`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1975).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 53, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 32 of 1985, s. 36, for Explanation (w.e.f. 1-4-1986).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 53 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `9. Sub-section ( 2 ) omitted by Act 20 of 1974, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-1975).`
