obj_root_law_sections_416_content:
  string
  line 416
  line `( i ) carrying on the business of banking or providing credit facilities to its members, or`
  line `( ii ) a cottage industry, or`
  line `1 [( iii ) the marketing of agricultural produce grown by its members, or]`
  line `( iv ) the purchase of agricultural implements, seeds, livestock or other articles intended for`
  line `agriculture for the purpose of supplying them to its members, or`
  line `( v ) the processing, without the aid of power, of the agricultural produce of its members, or`
  line `2 [( vi ) the collective disposal of the labour of its members, or`
  line `( vii ) fishing or allied activities, that is to say, the catching, curing, processing, preserving,`
  line `storing or marketing of fish or the purchase of materials and equipment in connection therewith`
  line `for the purpose of supplying them to its members,]`
  line `the whole of the amount of profits and gains of business attributable to any one or more of such`
  line `activities:`
  line `2 [Provided that in the case of a co-operative society falling under sub-clause ( vi ), or sub-clause ( vii ),`
  line `the rules and bye-laws of the society restrict the voting rights to the following classes of its members,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( 1 ) the individuals who contribute their labour or, as the case may be, carry on the fishing or`
  line `allied activities;`
  line `( 2 ) the co-operative credit societies which provide financial assistance to the society;`
  line `( 3 ) the State Government;]`
  line `3 [( b ) in the case of a co-operative society, being a primary society engaged in supplying milk,`
  line `oilseeds, fruits or vegetables raised or grown by its members to —`
  line `( i ) a federal co-operative society, being a society engaged in the business of supplying milk,`
  line `oilseeds, fruits, or vegetables, as the case may be; or`
  line `( ii ) the Government or a local authority; or`
  line `( iii ) a Government company as defined in section 617 of the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or a corporation established by or under a Central, State or Provincial Act`
  line `(being a company or corporation engaged in supplying milk, oilseeds, fruits or vegetables, as the`
  line `case may be, to the public),`
  line `the whole of the amount of profits and gains of such business;]`
  line `( c ) in the case of a co-operative society engaged in activities other than those specified in`
  line `clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) (either independently of, or in addition to, all or any of the activities so`
  line `specified), 4 [so much of its profits and gains attributable to such activities as does not exceed, —`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 11 of 1999, s. 8, for sub-clause ( iii ) (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1968).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 1971, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 11 of 1983, s. 30, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1984). Earlier substituted by Act 19 of 1978, s. 18`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1979).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 21 of 1979, s. 14, for “does not exceed twenty thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1980). Earlier substituted by`
  line `Act 14 of 1969, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-1970).`
