obj_root_law_sections_418_content:
  string
  line 418
  line `1 [( 4 ) The provisions of this section shall not apply in relation to any co-operative bank other than a`
  line `primary agricultural credit society or a primary co-operative agricultural and rural development bank.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, —`
  line `( a ) “co - operative bank” and “primary agricultural credit society” shall have the meanings`
  line `respectively assigned to them in Part V of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949);`
  line `( b ) “primary co - operative agricultural and rural development bank”means a society having its`
  line `area of operation confined to a taluk and the principal object of which is to provide for long-term`
  line `credit for agricultural and rural development activities.]`
  line `2 [ 80PA. Deduction in respect of certain income of Producer Companies. — ( 1 ) Where the gross`
  line `total income of an assessee, being a Producer Company having a total turnover of less than one hundred`
  line `crore rupees in any previous year, includes any profits and gains derived from eligible business, there`
  line `shall, in accordance with and subject to the provisions of this section, be allowed, in computing the total`
  line `income of the assessee, a deduction of an amount equal to one hundred per cent. of the profits and gains`
  line `attributable to such business for the previous year relevant to an assessment year commencing on or after`
  line `the 1st day of April, 2019, but before the 1st day of April, 2025.`
  line `( 2 ) In a case where the assessee is entitled also to deduction under any other provision of this`
  line `Chapter, the deduction under this section shall be allowed with reference to the income, if any, as referred`
  line `to in this section included in the gross total income as reduced by the deductions under such other`
  line `provision of this Chapter.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “eligible business” means—`
  line `( a ) the marketing of agricultural produce grown by the members; or`
  line `( b ) the purchase of agricultural implements, seeds, livestock or other articles intended for`
  line `agriculture for the purpose of supplying them to the members; or`
  line `( c ) the processing of the agricultural produce of the members;`
  line `( ii ) “member” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( d ) of section 581A of the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956;`
  line `( iii ) “Producer Company” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( l ) of section 581A of`
  line `the Companies Act, 1956.]`
  line `3 [ 80Q. Deduction in respect of profits and gains from the business of publication of books. — ( 1 )`
  line `Where in the case of an assessee the gross total income of the previous year relevant to the assessment`
  line `year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1992, or to any one of the four assessment years next following`
  line `that assessment year, includes any profits and gains derived from a business carried on in India of printing`
  line `and publication of books or publication of books, there shall, in accordance with and subject to the`
  line `provisions of this section, be allowed, in computing the total income of the assessee, a deduction from`
  line `such profits and gains of an amount equal to twenty per cent thereof.`
  line `( 2 ) In a case where the assessee is entitled also to the deduction under section 80HH or section`
  line `80HHA or section 80HHC or section 80-I or section 80-IA or section 80J or section 80P, in relation to`
  line `any part of the profits and gains referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), the deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be`
  line `allowed with reference to such profits and gains included in the gross total income as reduced by the`
  line `deductions under section 80HH, section 80HHA, section 80HHC, section 80-I, section 80-IA, section`
  line `80J and section 80P.`
  line `( 3 ) For the purposes of this section, “books” shall not include newspapers, journals, magazines,`
  line `diaries, brochures, tracts, pamphlets and other publications of a similar nature by whatever name called.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992). Earlier section 80Q omitted by Act 16 of 1972, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
