obj_root_law_sections_419_content:
  string
  line 419
  line `80QQ. [Deduction in respect of profits and gains from the business of publication of`
  line `books ]. — Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1987 (4 of 1987), s. 26 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `Original section was inserted by the Taxation Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1970 (42 of 1970),`
  line `s. 21 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `1 [ 80QQA. Deduction in respect of professional income of authors of text books in Indian`
  line `languages. — ( 1 ) Where, in the case of an individual resident in India, being an author, the gross total`
  line `income of the previous year relevant to the assessment year 2 [commencing on —`
  line `( a ) the 1st day of April, 1980, or to any one of the nine assessment years next following that`
  line `assessment year; or`
  line `( b ) the 1st day of April, 1992, or to any one of the four assessment years next following that`
  line `assessment year,]`
  line `includes any income derived by him in the exercise of his profession on account of any lump sum`
  line `consideration for the assignment or grant of any of his interests in the copyright of any book, or of`
  line `royalties or copyright fees (whether receivable in lump sum or otherwise) in respect of such book, there`
  line `shall, in accordance with and subject to the provisions of this section, be allowed, in computing the total`
  line `income of the assessee, a deduction from such income of an amount equal to twenty-five per cent.`
  line thereof.
  line `( 2 ) No deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be allowed unless —`
  line `( a ) the book is either in the nature of a dictionary, thesaurus or encyclopaedia or is one that has`
  line `been prescribed or recommended as a text book, or included in the curriculum, by any University, for`
  line `a degree or post-graduate course of that University; and`
  line `( b ) the book is written in any language specified in the Eighth Schedule to the Constitution or in`
  line `any such other language as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `specify in this behalf having regard to the need for promotion of publication of books of the nature`
  line `referred to in clause ( a ) in that language and other relevant factors.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “author” includes a joint author;`
  line `( ii ) “lump sum”, in regard to royalties or copyright fees, includes an advance payment on account`
  line `of such royalties or copyright fees which is not returnable;`
  line `( iii ) “University” shall have the same meaning as in the Explanation to clause ( ix ) of section 47.]`
  line `3 [ 80QQB. Deduction in respect of royalty income, etc., of authors of certain books other than`
  line `text-books. — ( 1 ) Where, in the case of an individual resident in India, being an author, the gross total`
  line `income includes any income, derived by him in the exercise of his profession, on account of any lump`
  line `sum consideration for the assignment or grant of any of his interests in the copyright of any book being a`
  line `work of literary, artistic or scientific nature, or of royalty or copyright fees (whether receivable in lump`
  line `sum or otherwise) in respect of such book, there shall, in accordance with and subject to the provisions of`
  line `this section, be allowed, in computing the total income of the assessee, a deduction from such income,`
  line `computed in the manner specified in sub-section ( 2 ).`
  line `( 2 ) The deduction under this section shall be equal to the whole of such income referred to in sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ), or an amount of three lakh rupees, whichever is less:`
  line `Provided that where the income by way of such royalty or the copyright fee, is not a lump sum`
  line `consideration in lieu of all rights of the assessee in the book, so much of the income, before allowing`
  line `expenses attributable to such income, as is in excess of fifteen per cent. of the value of such books sold`
  line `during the previous year shall be ignored:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1979, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-1980).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 36, for “commencing on the 1st day of April, 1980, or to any one of the nine assessment years`
  line `next following that assessment year, includes” (w.e.f. 1 -4- 1992). Earlier “nine” was substituted for “four” by Act 32 of`
  line `1985, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 44 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_419_footnotes:
