obj_root_law_sections_420_content:
  string
  line 420
  line `Provided further that in respect of any income earned from any source outside India, so much of the`
  line `income shall be taken into account for the purpose of this section as is brought into India by, or on behalf`
  line `of, the assessee in convertible foreign exchange within a period of six months from the end of the`
  line `previous year in which such income is earned or within such further period as the competent authority`
  line `may allow in this behalf.`
  line `( 3 ) No deduction under this section shall be allowed unless the assessee furnishes a certificate in the`
  line `prescribed form and in the prescribed manner, duly verified by any person responsible for making such`
  line `payment to the assessee as referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), along with the return of income, setting forth`
  line `such particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 4 ) No deduction under this section shall be allowed in respect of any income earned from any source`
  line `outside India, unless the assessee furnishes a certificate, in the prescribed form from the prescribed`
  line `authority, along with the return of income in the prescribed manner.`
  line `( 5 ) Where a deduction for any previous year has been claimed and allowed in respect of any income`
  line `referred to in this section, no deduction in respect of such income shall be allowed under any other`
  line `provision of this Act in any assessment year.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “author” includes a joint author;`
  line `( b ) “books” shall not include brochures, commentaries, diaries, guides, journals, magazines,`
  line `newspapers, pamphlets, text-books for schools, tracts and other publications of similar nature, by`
  line `whatever name called;`
  line `( c ) “competent authority” means the Reserve Bank of India or such other authority as is`
  line `authorised under any law for the time being in force for regulating payments and dealings in foreign`
  line exchange;
  line `( d ) “lump sum”, in regard to royalties or copyright fees, includes an advance payment on account`
  line `of such royalties or copyright fees which is not returnable.]`
  line `80R. Deduction in respect of remuneration from certain foreign sources in the case of`
  line `professors, teachers, etc. — Where the gross total income of an individual who is a citizen of India`
  line `includes any remuneration received by him outside India from any University or other educational`
  line `institution established outside India or 1 [any other association or body established outside India], for any`
  line `service rendered by him during his stay outside India in his capacity as a professor, teacher or research`
  line `worker in such University, institution, association or body, there shall be 2 [allowed, in computing the total`
  line `income of the individual, 3 [a deduction from such remuneration of an amount equal to —`
  line `( i ) sixty per cent. of such remuneration for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April,`
  line 2001;
  line `( ii ) forty-five per cent. of such remuneration for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2002;`
  line `( iii ) thirty per cent. of such remuneration for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2003;`
  line `( iv ) fifteen per cent. of such remuneration for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2004,`
  line `as is brought into India by, or on behalf of, the assessee in convertible foreign exchange within a period of`
  line `six months from the end of the previous year or within such further period as the competent authority may`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 11 of 1983, s. 31, for “such other association or body established outside India as may be notified in this`
  line `behalf by the Central Government in the Official Gazette” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1984).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 27, for “allowed a deduct ion from such remuneration of an amount equal to fifty per cent.`
  line `thereof, in computing the total income of the individual” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1991).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 42, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
