obj_root_law_sections_421_content:
  string
  line 421
  line `allow in this behalf and no deduction shall be allowed in respect of the assessment year beginning on the`
  line `1st day of April, 2005 and any subsequent assessment year:]]`
  line `Provided that no deduction under this section shall be allowed unless the assessee furnishes a`
  line `certificate, in the prescribed form, along with the return of income, certifying that the deduction has been`
  line `correctly claimed in accordance with the provisions of this section.]`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `2 [ Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, the expression “competent authority” means the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India or such other authority as is authorised under any law for the time being in force`
  line `for regulating payments and dealings in foreign exchange.]`
  line `3 [ 80RR. Deduction in respect of professional income from foreign sources in certain`
  line `cases. — Where the gross total income of an individual resident in India, being an author, playwright,`
  line `artist, 4 [musician, actor or sportsman (including an athlete)], includes any income derived by him in the`
  line `exercise of his profession from the Government of a foreign State or any person not resident in India,`
  line `5 [there shall be allowed, in computing the total income of the individual, 6 [a deduction from such income`
  line `of an amount equal to —`
  line `( i ) sixty per cent. of such income for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2001;`
  line `( ii ) forty-five per cent. of such income for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April,`
  line 2002;
  line `( iii ) thirty per cent. of such income for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April,`
  line 2003;
  line `( iv ) fifteen per cent. of such income for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April,`
  line 2004,
  line `as is brought into India by, or on behalf of, the assessee in convertible foreign exchange within a period of`
  line `six months from the end of the previous year or within such further period as the competent authority may`
  line `allow in this behalf and no deduction shall be allowed in respect of the assessment year beginning on the`
  line `1st day of April, 2005 and any subsequent assessment year:]`
  line `Provided that no deduction under this section shall be allowed unless the assessee furnishes a`
  line `certificate, in the prescribed form, along with the return of income, certifying that the deduction has been`
  line `correctly claimed in accordance with the provisions of this section.]]]`
  line `7 [ Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, the expression “competent authority” means the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India or such other authority as is authorised under any law for the time being in force`
  line `for regulating payments and dealings in foreign exchange.]`
  line `8 [ 80RRA. Deduction in respect of remuneration received for services rendered outside`
  line `India. — ( 1 ) Where the gross total income of an individual who is a citizen of India includes any`
  line `remuneration received by him in foreign currency from any employer (being a foreign employer or an`
  line `Indian concern) for any service rendered by him outside India, there shall, in accordance with and subject`
  line `1. The proviso omitted by Act 12 of 1990, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 54 ( w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 14 of 1969, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1970).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 20, for “musician or actor” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1980).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 28, for “and such income is received in, or brought into, India by him or on his behalf in`
  line `accordance with the Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1947, and any rules made thereunder, there shall be allowed a`
  line `deduction from such income of an amount equal to twenty-five per cent. of the income. so received or brought, in`
  line `computing the total income of the individual” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1991).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 43, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 55 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 19, for section 80RRA (w.e.f. 1-4-1978). Earlier section 80RRA inserted by Act 25 of 1975, s.`
  line `17 (w.e.f. 1-4-1975).`
