obj_root_law_sections_422_content:
  string
  line 422
  line `to the provisions of this section, be allowed, in computing the total income of the individual, 1 [a deduction`
  line `from such remuneration of an amount equal to —`
  line `( i ) sixty per cent. of such remuneration for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2001;`
  line `( ii ) forty-five per cent. of such remuneration for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2002;`
  line `( iii ) thirty per cent. of such remuneration for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2003;`
  line `( iv ) fifteen per cent. of such remuneration for an assessment year beginning on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2004,`
  line `as is brought into India by, or on behalf of, the assessee in convertible foreign exchange within a period of`
  line `six months from the end of the previous year or within such further period as the competent authority may`
  line `allow in this behalf and no deduction shall be allowed in respect of the assessment year beginning on the`
  line `1st day of April, 2005 and any subsequent assessment year:]`
  line `Provided that no deduction under this sub-section shall be allowed unless the assessee furnishes a`
  line `certificate, in the prescribed form, along with the return of income, certifying that the deduction has been`
  line `correctly claimed in accordance with the provisions of this section.]`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `( 2 ) The deduction under this section shall be allowed —`
  line `( i ) in the case of an individual who is or was, immediately before undertaking such service, in`
  line `the employment of the Central Government or any State Government, only if such service is`
  line `sponsored by the Central Government;`
  line `( ii ) in the case of any other individual, only if he is a technician and the terms and conditions of`
  line `his service outside India are approved in this behalf by the Central Government or the prescribed`
  line authority.
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “foreign currency” shall have the meaning assigned to it in the 3 [Foreign Exchange`
  line `Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999)];`
  line `( b ) “foreign employer” means,—`
  line `( i ) the Government of a foreign State; or`
  line `( ii ) a foreign enterprise; or`
  line `( iii ) any association or body established outside India;`
  line `( c ) “technician” means a person having specialised knowledge and experience in—`
  line `( i ) constructional or manufacturing operations or mining or the generation or distribution of`
  line `electricity or any other form of power; or`
  line `( ii ) agriculture, animal husbandry, dairy farming, deep sea fishing or ship building; or`
  line `( iii ) public administration or industrial or business management; or`
  line `( iv ) accountancy; or`
  line `( v ) any field of natural or applied science (including medical science) or social science; or`
  line `( vi ) any other field which the Board may prescribe in this behalf,`
  line `who is employed in a capacity in which such specialised knowledge and experience are actually utilised;`
  line `4 [( d ) “competent authority” means the Reserve Bank of India or such other authority as is`
  line `authorised under any law for the time being in force for regulating payments and dealings in foreign`
  line exchange.]
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 44, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `2. The proviso omitted by Act 12 of 1990, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 4, for “the Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 56 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
