obj_root_law_sections_423_content:
  string
  line 423
  line `1 [ 80RRB. Deduction in respect of royalty on patents. — ( 1 ) Where in the case of an assessee, being`
  line `an individual, who is —`
  line `( a ) resident in India;`
  line `( b ) a patentee;`
  line `( c ) in receipt of any income by way of royalty in respect of a patent registered on or after the 1st`
  line `day of April, 2003 under the Patents Act, 1970 (39 of 1970), and`
  line `his gross total income of the previous year includes royalty, there shall, in accordance with and subject to`
  line `the provisions of this section, be allowed a deduction, from such income, of an amount equal to the whole`
  line `of such income or three lakh rupees, whichever is less:`
  line `Provided that where a compulsory licence is granted in respect of any patent under the Patents Act,`
  line `1970 (39 of 1970), the income by way of royalty for the purpose of allowing deduction under this section`
  line `shall not exceed the amount of royalty under the terms and conditions of a licence settled by the`
  line `Controller under that Act:`
  line `Provided further that in respect of any income earned from any source outside India, so much of the`
  line `income, shall be taken into account for the purpose of this section as is brought into India by, or on behalf`
  line `of, the assessee in convertible foreign exchange within a period of six months from the end of the`
  line `previous year in which such income is earned or within such further period as the competent authority`
  line `referred to in clause ( c ) of the Explanation to section 80QQB may allow in this behalf.`
  line `( 2 ) No deduction under this section shall be allowed unless the assessee furnishes a certificate in the`
  line `prescribed form, duly signed by the prescribed authority, along with the return of income setting forth`
  line `such particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 3 ) No deduction under this section shall be allowed in respect of any income earned from any source`
  line `outside India, unless the assessee furnishes a certificate in the prescribed form, from the authority or`
  line `authorities, as may be prescribed, along with the return of income.`
  line `( 4 ) Where a deduction for any previous year has been claimed and allowed in respect of any income`
  line `referred to in this section, no deduction in respect of such income shall be allowed, under any other`
  line `provision of this Act in any assessment year.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “Controller” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 2`
  line `of the Patents Act, 1970 (39 of 1970);`
  line `( b ) “lump sum” includes an advance payment on account of such royalties which is not`
  line returnable;
  line `( c ) “patent” means a patent (including a patent of addition) granted under the Patents Act, 1970`
  line `(39 of 1970);`
  line `( d ) “patentee” means the person, being the true and first inventor of the invention, whose name is`
  line `entered on the patent register as the patentee, in accordance with the Patents Act, 1970 (39 of 1970),`
  line `and includes every such person, being the true and first inventor of the invention, where more than`
  line `one person is registered as patentee under that Act in respect of that patent;`
  line `( e ) “patent of addition” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( q ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 2 of the Patents Act, 1970 (39 of 1970);`
  line `( f ) “patented article” and “patented process” shall have the meanings respectively assigned to`
  line `them in clause ( o ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 2 of the Patents Act, 1970 (39 of 1970);`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_423_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_424:
