  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_424_footnotes
  sourcePage 424
obj_root_law_sections_424_content:
  string
  line 424
  line `( g ) “royalty”, in respect of a patent, means consideration (including any lump sum consideration`
  line `but excluding any consideration which would be the income of the recipient chargeable under the`
  line `head “Capital gains” or consideration for sale of product manufactured with the use of patented`
  line `process or of the patented article for commercial use) for —`
  line `( i ) the transfer of all or any rights (including the granting of a licence) in respect of a patent;`
  line or
  line `( ii ) the imparting of any information concerning the working of, or the use of, a patent; or`
  line `( iii ) the use of any patent; or`
  line `( iv ) the rendering of any services in connection with the activities referred to in sub-clauses`
  line `( i ) to ( iii );`
  line `( h ) “true and first inventor” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( y ) of sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 2 of the Patents Act, 1970 (39 of 1970).]`
  line `80S. [ Deduction in respect of compensation for termination of managing agency, etc., in the case of`
  line `assessees other than companies.] Omitted by the Finance Act, 1986 (23 of 1986), s. 22 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `Original section was introduced in place of old section 112 by the Finance ( No. 2) Act, 1967 (20 of`
  line `1967), s. 33 and the Third Schedule ( w.e.f. 1-4-1968).`
  line `80T. [ Deduction in respect of long-term capital gains in the case of assessees other than companies. ]`
  line `Omitted by the Finance Act, 1987 (11 of 1987), s. 38 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988). Original section was inserted by`
  line `the Finance ( No. 2) Act, 1967 (20 of 1967), s. 33 and the Third Schedule ( w.e.f. 1-4-1968) in replacement`
  line `of section 114.`
  line `80TT. [ Deduction in respect of winnings from lottery.] Omitted by the Finance Act, 1986 (23 of`
  line `1986), s. 24 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1987). Original section was inserted by the Finance Act, 1972 (16 of 1972), s. 22`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1972) and amended by the Finance ( No. 2) Act, 1980, ( w.e.f. 1-4-1981).`
  line `1 [ CA. — Deductions in respect of other incomes`
  line `80TTA.Deduction in respect of interest on deposits in savings account. — ( 1 ) Where the gross total`
  line `income of an assesse 2 [(other than the assessee referred to in section 80TTB)], being an individual or a`
  line `Hindu undivided family, includes any income by way of interest on deposits (not being time deposits) in a`
  line `savings account with —`
  line `( a ) a banking company to which the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), applies`
  line `(including any bank or banking institution referred to in section 51 of that Act);`
  line `( b ) a co-operative society engaged in carrying on the business of banking (including a`
  line `co-operative land mortgage bank or a co-operative land development bank); or`
  line `( c ) a Post Office as defined in clause ( k ) of section 2 of the Indian Post Office Act, 1898 (6 of`
  line `1898),`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_424_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_425:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-425
  sectionNo (425)
  orderNo 425
  title `Page 425`
  content obj_root_law_sections_425_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_425_footnotes
  sourcePage 425
obj_root_law_sections_425_content:
  string
  line 425
  line `there shall, in accordance with and subject to the provisions of this section, be allowed, in computing`
  line `the total income of the assessee a deduction as specified hereunder, namely: —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the amount of such income does not exceed in the aggregate ten thousand`
  line `rupees, the whole of such amount; and`
  line `( ii ) in any other case, ten thousand rupees.`
  line `( 2 ) Where the income referred to in this section is derived from any deposit in a savings account held`
  line `by, or on behalf of, a firm, an association of persons or a body of individuals, no deduction shall be`
  line `allowed under this section in respect of such income in computing the total income of any partner of the`
  line `firm or any member of the association or any individual of the body.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, “time deposits” means the deposits repayable on`
  line `expiry of fixed periods.]`
  line `1 [ 80TTB. Deduction in respect of interest on deposits in case of senior citizens. — ( 1 ) Where the`
  line `gross total income of an assessee, being a senior citizen, includes any income by way of interest on`
  line `deposits with —`
  line `( a ) a banking company to which the Banking Regulation Act, 1949, applies (including any bank`
  line `or banking institution referred to in section 51 of that Act);`
  line `( b ) a co-operative society engaged in carrying on the business of banking (including a co-`
  line `operative land mortgage bank or a co-operative land development bank); or`
  line `( c ) a Post Office as defined in clause ( k ) of section 2 of the Indian Post Office Act, 1898,`
  line `there shall, in accordance with and subject to the provisions of this section, be allowed, in computing the`
  line `total income of the assessee, a deduction —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the amount of such income does not exceed in the aggregate fifty thousand`
  line `rupees, the whole of such amount; and`
  line `( ii ) in any other case, fifty thousand rupees.`
  line `( 2 ) Where the income referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) is derived from any deposit held by, or on behalf`
  line `of, a firm, an association of persons or a body of individuals, no deduction shall be allowed under this`
  line `section in respect of such income in computing the total income of any partner of the firm or any member`
  line `of the association or any individual of the body.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, “senior citizen” means an individual resident in India`
  line `who is of the age of sixty years or more at any time during the relevant previous year.]`
  line `2 [ D. — Other deductions`
  line `80U. 3 [ Deduction in case of a person with disability. — 4 [( 1 ) In computing the total income of an`
  line `individual, being a resident, who, at any time during the previous year, is certified by the medical`
  line `authority to be a person with disability, there shall be allowed a deduction of a sum of seventy-five`
  line `thousand rupees:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 19 of 1968, s. 30 and the Third Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-1969).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 46, for section 80U (w.e.f. 1-4-2004). Earlier substituted by Act 49 of 1991, s. 37`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 24, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_425_footnotes:
