obj_root_law_sections_426_content:
  string
  line 426
  line `Provided that where such individual is a person with severe disability, the provisions of this`
  line `sub- section shall have effect as if for the words “seventy - five thousand rupees”, the words “one hundred`
  line `and twenty- five thousand rupees” had been substituted. ]`
  line `( 2 ) Every individual claiming a deduction under this section shall furnish a copy of the certificate`
  line `issued by the medical authority in the form and manner, as may be prescribed, along with the return of`
  line `income under section 139, in respect of the assessment year for which the deduction is claimed:`
  line `Provided that where the condition of disability requires reassessment of its extent after a period`
  line `stipulated in the aforesaid certificate, no deduction under this section shall be allowed for any assessment`
  line `year relating to any previous year beginning after the expiry of the previous year during which the`
  line `aforesaid certificate of disability had expired, unless a new certificate is obtained from the medical`
  line `authority in the form and manner, as may be prescribed, and a copy thereof is furnished along with the`
  line `return of income under section 139.`
  line `1 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “disability” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( i ) of section 2 of the Persons with`
  line `Disabilities (Equal Opportunities, Protection of Rights and Full Participation) Act, 1995 (1 of 1996),`
  line `and includes “autism”, “cerebral palsy” and “multiple disabilities” referred to in clauses ( a ), ( c ) and`
  line `( h ) of section 2 of the National Trust for Welfare of Persons with Autism, Cerebral Palsy, Mental`
  line `Retardation and Multiple Disabilities Act, 1999 (44 of 1999);`
  line `( b ) “medical authority” means the medical authority as referred to in clause ( p ) of section 2 of`
  line `the Persons with Disabilities (Equal Opportunities, Protection of Rights and Full Participation) Act,`
  line `1995 (1 of 1996), or such other medical authority as may, by notification, be specified by the Central`
  line `Government for certifying “autism”, “cerebral palsy”, “multiple disabilities”, “person with disability”`
  line `and “severe disability” referred to in clauses ( a ), ( c ), ( h ), ( j ) and ( o ) of section 2 of the National Trust`
  line `for Welfare of Persons with Autism, Cerebral Palsy, Mental Retardation and Multiple Disabilities`
  line `Act, 1999 (44 of 1999);`
  line `( c ) “person with disability” means a person referred to in clause ( t ) of section 2 of the Persons`
  line `with Disabilities (Equal Opportunities, Protection of Rights and Full Participation) Act, 1995 (1 of`
  line `1996), or clause ( j ) of section 2 of the National Trust for Welfare of Persons with Autism, Cerebral`
  line `Palsy, Mental Retardation and Multiple Disabilities Act, 1999 (44 of 1999);`
  line `( d ) “person with severe disability” means—`
  line `( i ) a person with eighty per cent or more of one or more disabilities, as referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 4 ) of section 56 of the Persons with Disabilities (Equal Opportunities, Protection of`
  line `Rights and Full Participation) Act, 1995 (1 of 1996); or`
  line `( ii ) a person with severe disability referred to in clause ( o ) of section 2 of the National Trust`
  line `for Welfare of Persons with Autism, Cerebral Palsy, Mental Retardation and Multiple Disabilities`
  line `Act, 1999 (44 of 1999).]]`
  line `80V. [ Deduction from gross total income of the parent in certain cases.] Omitted by the Finance Act,`
  line `1994 (32 of 1994), s. 28( w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
  line `80VV. [ Deduction in respect of expenses incurred in connection with certain proceedings under the`
  line `Act.] Omitted by the Finance Act, 1985 (32 of 1985), s. 25 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1986). Original section was inserted`
  line `by the Taxation Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1975 (41 of 1975), s. 26( w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 19, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
