obj_root_law_sections_428_content:
  string
  line 428
  line `( 2 ) The aggregate amount of the deductions under 1 [section 87A or section 88] or section`
  line `88A 2 [or section 88B] 3 [or section 88C] 4 [or section 88D or section 88E] shall not, in any case, exceed the`
  line `amount of income-tax (as computed before allowing the deductions under this Chapter) on the total`
  line `income of the assessee with which he is chargeable for any assessment year.`
  line `5 [87A. Rebate of income-tax in case of certain individuals. — An assessee, being an individual`
  line `resident in India, whose total income does not exceed 6 [ 7 [five hundred thousand] rupees], shall be entitled`
  line `to a deduction, from the amount of income-tax (as computed before allowing the deductions under this`
  line `Chapter) on his total income with which he is chargeable for any assessment year, of an amount equal to`
  line `hundred per cent of such income-tax or an amount of 8 [ 9 [twelve thousand and five hundred] rupees],`
  line `whichever is less.]`
  line `88. Rebate on life insurance premia, contribution to provident fund, etc. — 10 [( 1 ) Subject to the`
  line `provisions of this section, an assessee, being an individual, or a Hindu undivided family, shall be entitled`
  line `to a deduction, from the amount of income-tax (as computed before allowing the deductions under this`
  line `Chapter) on his total income with which he is chargeable for any assessment year, of an amount equal`
  line `to —`
  line `( i ) in the case of an individual or a Hindu undivided family, whose gross total income before`
  line `giving effect to deductions under Chapter VI-A, is one lakh fifty thousand rupees or less, twenty per`
  line `cent of the aggregate of the sums referred to in sub-section ( 2 ):`
  line `Provided that an individual shall be entitled to a deduction of an amount equal to thirty per cent`
  line `of the aggregate of the sums referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) if his income under the head “Salaries”—`
  line `( a ) does not exceed one lakh rupees during the previous year before allowing the deduction`
  line `under section 16; and`
  line `( b ) is not less than ninety per cent of his gross total income, as defined in sub-section ( 5 )`
  line `of section 80B;`
  line `( ii ) in the case of an individual or a Hindu undivided family, whose gross total income before`
  line `giving effect to deductions under Chapter VI-A, is more than one lakh fifty thousand rupees but does`
  line `not exceed five lakh rupees, fifteen per cent of the aggregate of the sums referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 2 );`
  line `( iii ) in the case of an individual or a Hindu undivided family, whose gross total income before`
  line `giving effect to deductions under Chapter VI-A, exceeds five lakh rupees, nil.]`
  line `( 2 ) The sums referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be any sums paid or deposited in the previous year by`
  line `the assessee 11 *** —`
  line `( i ) to effect or to keep in force an insurance on the life of persons specified in sub-section ( 4 );`
  line `( ii ) to effect or to keep in force a contract for a deferred annuity, 12 [not being an annuity plan`
  line `referred to in clause ( xiiia )], on the life of persons specified in sub-section ( 4 ):`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 21, for “section 88” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2014).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 38, for “five hundred thousand rupees” w.e.f. 1 -4-2018).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 8, for “three hundred fifty thousand” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2020).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 38, for “ five thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4- 2018) and by Act 28 of 2016, s. 46, for “two`
  line `thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 8, for “two thousand and five hundred” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2020).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 37, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2003). Earlier sub-section ( 1 ) was amended by`
  line `Act 12 of 1990, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991), Act 18 of 1992, s. 51 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993), Act 32 of 1994, s. 29 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1991)`
  line `and Act 14 of 2001, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `11. The words “out of his income chargeable to tax” omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 37 (w.e.f. 1 -4-2003).`
  line `12. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 51, for “not being an annuity plan referred to in clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 80CCA” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1993).`
