obj_root_law_sections_431_content:
  string
  line 431
  line `( 6 ) any company in which the public are substantially interested or any co-operative`
  line `society, where such company or co-operative society is engaged in the business of financing`
  line `the construction of houses, or`
  line `1 [( 6A ) the assessee’s employer where such employer is an author ity or a board or a`
  line `corporation or any other body established or constituted under a Central or State Act, or]`
  line `( 7 ) the assessee’s employer where such employer is a public company or a public sector`
  line `company or a University established by law or a college affiliated to such University or a`
  line `local authority 2 [or a co-operative society];`
  line `( d ) stamp duty, registration fee and other expenses for the purpose of transfer of such house`
  line `property to the assessee,`
  line `but shall not include any payment towards or by way of —`
  line `( A ) the admission fee, cost of share and initial deposit which a shareholder of a company or a`
  line `member of a co-operative society has to pay for becoming such shareholder or member; or`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `( C ) the cost of any addition or alteration to, or renovation or repair of, the house property`
  line `which is carried out after the issue of the completion certificate in respect of the house property`
  line `by the authority competent to issue such certificate or after the house property or any part thereof`
  line `has either been occupied by the assessee or any other person on his behalf or been let out; or`
  line `( D ) any expenditure in respect of which deduction is allowable under the provisions`
  line `of section 24;`
  line `4 [( xvi ) as subscription to equity shares or debentures forming part of any eligible issue of capital`
  line `approved by the Board on an application made by a public company 5 [or as subscription to any`
  line `eligible issue of capital by any public financial institution] in the prescribed form:`
  line `Provided that where a deduction is claimed and allowed under this clause with reference to the`
  line `cost of any equity shares or debentures, the cost of such shares or debentures shall not be taken into`
  line `account for the purposes of sections 54EA and 54EB.`
  line `6 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( i ) “eligible issue of capital” means an issue made by a public company formed and registered`
  line `in India or a public financial institution and the entire proceeds of the issue are utilised wholly`
  line `and exclusively for the purposes of any business referred to in sub-section ( 4 ) of section 80-IA;`
  line `( ii ) “public company” shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 3 of the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line `( iii ) “public financial institution” shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 4A of the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);]]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 51 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `3. Clause ( B ) omitted by Act 49 of 1991, s. 38 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-4-1997).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 47, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-4-2004). Earlier it was amended by Act 33 of 1996, s. 34`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1997), Act 26 of 1997, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998), Act 27 of 1999, s. 90 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
