obj_root_law_sections_432_content:
  string
  line 432
  line `( xvii ) as subscription to any units of any mutual fund referred to in clause ( 23D ) of section 10 and`
  line `approved by the Board on an application made by such mutual fund in the prescribed form:`
  line `Provided that where a deduction is claimed and allowed under this clause with reference to the`
  line `cost of units, the cost of such units shall not be taken into account for the purposes of sections`
  line `54EA and 54EB:`
  line `Provided further that this clause shall apply if the amount of subscription to such units is`
  line `subscribed only in the eligible issue of capital of any company.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause “eligible issue of capital” means an issue referred`
  line `to in clause ( i ) of the Explanation to clause ( xvi ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 88.`
  line `1 [( 2A ) The provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) shall apply only to so much of any premium or other`
  line `payment made on an insurance policy other than a contract for a deferred annuity as is not in excess of`
  line `twenty per cent of the actual capital sum assured.`
  line `Explanation. — In calculating any such actual capital sum, no account shall be taken —`
  line `( i ) of the value of any premiums agreed to be returned, or`
  line `( ii ) of any benefit by way of bonus or otherwise over and above the sum actually assured, which`
  line `is to be, or, may be, received under the policy by any person.]`
  line `2 [( 3 ) The sums referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) shall be paid or deposited at any time during the previous`
  line `year, and the assessee, being an individual or a Hindu undivided family, shall be entitled to a deduction`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) on so much of the aggregate of such sums paid or deposited as does not exceed the`
  line `total income of the assessee, chargeable to tax during the relevant previous year.]`
  line `( 4 ) The persons referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) shall be the following, namely: —`
  line `3 [( a ) for the purposes of clauses ( i ), ( v ), ( xii ) and ( xiii ) of that sub-section, —`
  line `( i ) in the case of an individual, the individual, the wife or husband and any child of such`
  line `individual, and`
  line `( ii ) in the case of a Hindu undivided family, any member thereof;]`
  line `( b ) for the purposes of clause ( ii ) of that sub-section, —`
  line `( i ) in the case of an individual, the individual, the wife or husband and any child of such`
  line `individual, and`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `( c ) for the purposes of 5 [clause ( viii )] of that sub-section, —`
  line `( i ) in the case of an individual, such individual or a minor of whom he is the guardian;`
  line `( ii ) in the case of a Hindu undivided family, any member of the family;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003). Earlier sub-section ( 3 ) was omitted by Act 22 of 1995, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-4-`
  line `1996).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 29, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `4. Sub-clause ( ii ) omitted by s. 29, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 29, ibid., for “clauses ( v ) and ( viii )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1991).`
