obj_root_law_sections_433_content:
  string
  line 433
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `2 [( d ) for the purpose of clause ( xivb ) of that sub-section, in the case of an individual, any two`
  line `children of such individual.]`
  line `3 [( 5 ) Where the aggregate of any sums specified in clause ( i ) to clause ( xvii ) of sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `exceeds an amount of one hundred thousand rupees, a deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be allowed`
  line `with reference to so much of the aggregate as does not exceed an amount of one hundred thousand`
  line `rupees:`
  line `Provided that where the aggregate of any sums specified in clause ( i ) to clause ( xv ) of sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `exceeds an amount of seventy thousand rupees, a deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) in respect of such sums`
  line `shall be allowed with reference to so much of the aggregate as does not exceed an amount of seventy`
  line `thousand rupees:`
  line `Provided further that where the aggregate of any sums specified in clause ( xv ) of sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `exceeds an amount of twenty thousand rupees, a deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) in respect of such sums`
  line `shall be allowed with reference to so much of the aggregate as does not exceed an amount of twenty`
  line `thousand rupees:`
  line `4 [Provided also that where the aggregate of any sum specified in clause ( xivb ) of sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `exceeds an amount of twelve thousand rupees in respect of a child, a deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) in`
  line `respect of such sum shall be allowed with reference to so much of the aggregate as does not exceed an`
  line `amount of twelve thousand rupees in respect of such child.]`
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `( 7 ) Where, in any previous year, an assessee —`
  line `( i ) terminates his contract of insurance referred to in clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 2 ), by notice to`
  line `that effect or where the contract ceases to be in force by reason of failure to pay any premium, by not`
  line `reviving 6 [contract of insurance, —`
  line `( a ) in case of any single premium policy, within two years after the date of commencement`
  line `of insurance; or`
  line `( b ) in any other case, before premiums have been paid for two years; or]`
  line `( ii ) terminates his participation in any unit-linked insurance plan referred to in clause ( xii ) or`
  line `clause ( xiii ) of sub-section ( 2 ), by notice to that effect or where he ceases to participate by reason of`
  line `failure to pay any contribution, by not reviving his participation, before contributions in respect of`
  line `such participation have been paid for five years; or`
  line `( iii ) transfers the house property referred to in clause ( xv ) of sub-section ( 2 ) before the expiry of`
  line `five years from the end of the financial year in which possession of such property is obtained by him,`
  line `or receives back, whether by way of refund or otherwise, any sum specified in that clause,`
  line `1. Sub-clause ( iii ) omitted by Act 32 of 1994, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004). Earlier clause ( d ) omitted by Act 32 of 1994, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 37, for sub-section ( 5 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `5. Sub-sections ( 5A ) and ( 6 ) omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 22, for “contract of insurance, before premiums have been paid for two years; or”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1996).`
