obj_root_law_sections_434_content:
  string
  line 434
  line `then, —`
  line `( a ) no deduction shall be allowed to the assessee under sub-section ( 1 ) with reference to any of`
  line `the sums, referred to in clauses ( i ), ( xii ), ( xiii ) and ( xv ) of sub-section ( 2 ), paid in such previous year;`
  line and
  line `( b ) the aggregate amount of the deductions of income-tax so allowed in respect of the previous`
  line `year or years preceding such previous year, shall be deemed to be tax payable by the assessee in the`
  line `assessment year relevant to such previous year and shall be added to the tax on the total income of the`
  line `assessee with which he is chargeable for such assessment year.`
  line `1 [( 7A ) If any equity shares or debentures, with reference to the cost of which a deduction is allowed`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ), are sold or otherwise transferred by the assessee to any person at any time within a`
  line `period of three years from the date of their acquisition, the aggregate amount of the deductions of income-`
  line `tax so allowed in respect of such equity shares or debentures in the previous year or years preceding the`
  line `previous year in which such sale or transfer has taken place shall be deemed to be tax payable by the`
  line `assessee for the assessment year relevant to such previous year and shall be added to the amount of`
  line `income-tax on the total income of the assessee with which he is chargeable for such assessment year.`
  line `Explanation. — A person shall be treated as having acquired any shares or debentures on the date on`
  line `which his name is entered in relation to those shares or debentures in the register of members or of`
  line `debenture-holders, as the case may be, of the public company.]`
  line `( 8 ) In this section, —`
  line `( i ) “contribution” to any fund shall not include any sums in repayment of loan;`
  line `( ii ) “insurance” shall include—`
  line `( a ) a policy of insurance on the life of an individual or the spouse or the child of such`
  line `individual or a member of a Hindu undivided family securing the payment of specified sum on`
  line `the stipulated date of maturity, if such person is alive on such date notwithstanding that the policy`
  line `of insurance provides only for the return of premiums paid (with or without any interest thereon)`
  line `in the event of such person dying before the said stipulated date;`
  line `( b ) a policy of insurance effected by an individual or a member of a Hindu undivided family`
  line `for the benefit of a minor with the object of enabling the minor, after he has attained majority to`
  line `secure insurance on his own life by adopting the policy and on his being alive on a date (after`
  line `such adoption) specified in the policy in this behalf;`
  line `( iii ) “Life Insurance Corporation” means the Life Insurance Corporation of India established`
  line `under the Life Insurance Corporation Act, 1956 (31 of 1956);`
  line `( iv ) “public company” shall have the same meaning as in section 3 of the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line `( v ) “security” means a Government security as defined in clause ( 2 ) of section 2 of the Public`
  line `Debt Act, 1944 (18 of 1944);`
  line `( vi ) “transfer” shall be deemed to include also the transactions referred to in clause ( f ) of`
  line `section 269UA.`
  line `2 [( 9 ) No deduction from the amount of income-tax shall be allowed under this section to an assessee,`
  line `being an individual or a Hindu undivided family for the assessment year beginning on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2006 and subsequent years.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-4-1997).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
