obj_root_law_sections_435_content:
  string
  line 435
  line `88A. [ Rebate in respect of investment in certain new shares or units ]. — Omitted by the`
  line `Finance ( No. 2) Act (33 of 1996), s. 35 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1994).`
  line `88B. [ Rebate of income-tax in case of individuals of sixty-five years or above]. — Omitted by the`
  line `Finance Act, 2005 (18 of 2005), s. 30 ( w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `88C. [Rebate of income-tax in case of women below sixty-five years]. — Omitted by s. 31, ibid.,`
  line `( w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `88D. [ Rebate of income-tax in case of certain individuals]. — Omitted by s. 32, ibid., ( w.e.f. 1-4-`
  line `2006).`
  line `1 [88E. Rebate in respect of securities transaction tax. — ( 1 ) Where the total income of an assessee`
  line `in a previous year includes any income, chargeable under the head “Profits and gains of business or`
  line `profession”, arising from taxable securities transactions, he shall be entitled to a deduction, from the`
  line `amount of income-tax on such income arising from such transactions, computed in the manner provided`
  line `in sub-section ( 2 ), of an amount equal to the securities transaction tax paid by him in respect of the`
  line `taxable securities transactions entered into in the course of his business during that previous year:`
  line `Provided that no deduction under this sub-section shall be allowed unless the assessee furnishes along`
  line `with the return of income, evidence of payment of securities transaction tax in the prescribed form:`
  line `Provided further that the amount of deduction under this sub-section shall not exceed the amount of`
  line `income-tax on such income computed in the manner provided in sub-section ( 2 ).`
  line `( 2 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), the amount of income-tax on the income arising from the`
  line `taxable securities transactions, referred to in that sub-section, shall be equal to the amount calculated by`
  line `applying the average rate of income-tax on such income.`
  line `2 [( 3 ) No deduction under this section shall be allowed in, or after, the assessment year beginning on`
  line `the 1st day of April, 2009.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, the expressions, “taxable securities transaction” and`
  line `“securities transaction tax” shall have the same meanings respectively assigned to them under Chapter`
  line `VII of the Finance (No. 2) Act, 2004.]`
  line `B. — Relief for income-tax]`
  line `3 [89. Relief when salary, etc., is paid in arrears or in advance. — Where an assessee is in receipt of`
  line `a sum in the nature of salary, being paid in arrears or in advance or is in receipt, in any one financial year,`
  line `of salary for more than twelve months or a payment which under the provisions of clause ( 3 ) of section`
  line `17 is a profit in lieu of salary, or is in receipt of a sum in the nature of family pension as defined in`
  line `the Explanation to clause ( iia ) of section 57, being paid in arrears, due to which his total income is`
  line `assessed at a rate higher than that at which it would otherwise have been assessed, the Assessing Officer`
  line `shall, on an application made to him in this behalf, grant such relief as may be prescribed:]`
  line `4 [Provided that no such relief shall be granted in respect of any amount received or receivable by an`
  line `assessee on his voluntary retirement or termination of his service, in accordance with any scheme or`
  line `schemes of voluntary retirement or in the case of a public sector company referred to in sub-clause ( i ) of`
  line `clause ( 10C ) of section 10, a scheme of voluntary separation, if an exemption in respect of any amount`
  line `received or receivable on such voluntary retirement or termination of his service or voluntary separation`
  line `has been claimed by the assessee under clause ( 10C ) of section 10 in respect of such, or any other,`
  line `assessment year.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 23, for section 88E (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s.38, for section 89 (w.e.f. 1-4-1996). Earlier section substituted by42 of 1970, s. 23`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 39 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
