obj_root_law_sections_436_content:
  string
  line 436
  line `89A. [ Tax relief in relation to export turnover ]. — Omitted by the Finance Act, 1983 (11 of 1983),`
  line `s. 33 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1983). The provisions of this section were later substituted by scheme contained in`
  line `section 80 HHC, inserted by the Finance Act, 1983 (11 of 1983), s. 24 ( w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1983). Originally section`
  line `89 A was inserted by the Finance Act, 1982 (29 of 1983), s. 22 ( w.e.f. 1-6-1982).`
  line `CHAPTER IX`
  line `DOUBLE TAXATION RELIEF`
  line `1 [90. Agreement with foreign countries or specified territories. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may`
  line `enter into an agreement with the Government of any country outside India or specified territory outside`
  line `India, —`
  line `( a ) for the granting of relief in respect of —`
  line `( i ) income on which have been paid both income-tax under this Act and income-tax in that`
  line `country or specified territory, as the case may be, or`
  line `( ii ) income-tax chargeable under this Act and under the corresponding law in force in that`
  line `country or specified territory, as the case may be, to promote mutual economic relations, trade`
  line `and investment, or`
  line `( b ) for the avoidance of double taxation of income under this Act and under the corresponding`
  line `law in force in that country or specified territory, as the case may be, or`
  line `( c ) for exchange of information for the prevention of evasion or avoidance of income-tax`
  line `chargeable under this Act or under the corresponding law in force in that country or specified`
  line `territory, as the case may be, or investigation of cases of such evasion or avoidance, or`
  line `( d ) for recovery of income-tax under this Act and under the corresponding law in force in that`
  line `country or specified territory, as the case may be,`
  line `and may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make such provisions as may be necessary for`
  line `implementing the agreement.`
  line `( 2 ) Where the Central Government has entered into an agreement with the Government of any`
  line `country outside India or specified territory outside India, as the case may be, under sub-section ( 1 ) for`
  line `granting relief of tax, or as the case may be, avoidance of double taxation, then, in relation to the assessee`
  line `to whom such agreement applies, the provisions of this Act shall apply to the extent they are more`
  line `beneficial to that assessee.`
  line `2 [( 2A ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 2 ), the provisions of Chapter X A of the`
  line `Act shall apply to the assessee even if such provisions are not beneficial to him.]`
  line `( 3 ) Any term used but not defined in this Act or in the agreement referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall,`
  line `unless the context otherwise requires, and is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act or the`
  line `agreement, have the same meaning as assigned to it in the notification issued by the Central Government`
  line `in the Official Gazette in this behalf.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 40, for section 90 (w.e.f. 1-10-2009). Earlier section amended by Act 16 of 1972, s. 23`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1972). Further amended by Act 49 of 1991, s. 39 (w.e.f. 1-4-1972). Earlier substituted by Act 14 of 2001, s. 90`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016). Earlier inserted by Act 23 of 2012, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013), and later on`
  line `omitted by Act 17 of 2013, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
