obj_root_law_sections_437_content:
  string
  line 437
  line `1 [( 4 ) An assessee, not being a resident, to whom an agreement referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) applies,`
  line `shall not be entitled to claim any relief under such agreement unless 2 [a certificate of his being a resident]`
  line `in any country outside India or specified territory outside India, as the case may be, is obtained by him`
  line `from the Government of that country or specified territory.]`
  line `3 [( 5 ) The assessee referred to in sub-section ( 4 ) shall also provide such other documents and`
  line `information, as may be prescribed.]`
  line `Explanation 1. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the charge of tax in respect of a`
  line `foreign company at a rate higher than the rate at which a domestic company is chargeable, shall not be`
  line `regarded as less favourable charge or levy of tax in respect of such foreign company.`
  line `Explanation 2. —For the purposes of this section, “specified territory” means any area outside India`
  line `which may be notified as such by the Central Government.`
  line `4 [ Explanation 3. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that where any term is used in any`
  line `agreement entered into under sub-section ( 1 ) and not defined under the said agreement or the Act, but is`
  line `assigned a meaning to it in the notification issued under sub-section ( 3 ) and the notification issued`
  line `thereunder being in force, then, the meaning assigned to such term shall be deemed to have effect from`
  line `the date on which the said agreement came into force.]`
  line `5 [ Explanation 4. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that where any term used in an`
  line `agreement entered into under sub-section ( 1 ) is defined under the said agreement, the said term shall have`
  line `the same meaning as assigned to it in the agreement; and where the term is not defined in the said`
  line `agreement, but defined in the Act, it shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in the Act and`
  line `explanation, if any, given to it by the Central Government. ]`
  line `6 [90A. Adoption by Central Government of agreement between specified associations for double`
  line `taxation relief. — ( 1 ) Any specified association in India may enter into an agreement with any specified`
  line `association in the specified territory outside India and the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, make such provisions as may be necessary for adopting and implementing such`
  line `agreement —`
  line `( a ) for the granting of relief in respect of —`
  line `( i ) income on which have been paid both income-tax under this Act and income-tax in any`
  line `specified territory outside India; or`
  line `( ii ) income-tax chargeable under this Act and under the corresponding law in force in that`
  line `specified territory outside India to promote mutual economic relations, trade and investment, or`
  line `( b ) for the avoidance of double taxation of income under this Act and under the corresponding`
  line `law in force in that specified territory outside India, or`
  line `( c ) for exchange of information for the prevention of evasion or avoidance of income-tax`
  line `chargeable under this Act or under the corresponding law in force in that specified territory outside`
  line `India, or investigation of cases of such evasion or avoidance, or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 23, for “a certificate, containing such particulars as may be prescribed, of his being a resident”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `4. The Explanation 3 inserted by Act 23 of 2012, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-10-2009).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 39 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-6-2006).`
