  line 438
  line `( d ) for recovery of income-tax under this Act and under the corresponding law in force in that`
  line `specified territory outside India.`
  line `( 2 ) Where a specified association in India has entered into an agreement with a specified association`
  line `of any specified territory outside India under sub-section ( 1 ) and such agreement has been notified under`
  line `that sub-section, for granting relief of tax, or as the case may be, avoidance of double taxation, then, in`
  line `relation to the assessee to whom such agreement applies, the provisions of this Act shall apply to the`
  line `extent they are more beneficial to that assessee.`
  line `1 [( 2A ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 2 ), the provisions of Chapter XA of the`
  line `Act shall apply to the assessee even if such provisions are not beneficial to him.]`
  line `( 3 ) Any term used but not defined in this Act or in the agreement referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall,`
  line `unless the context otherwise requires, and is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act or the`
  line `agreement, have the same meaning as assigned to it in the notification issued by the Central Government`
  line `in the Official Gazette in this behalf.`
  line `2 [( 4 ) An assessee, not being a resident, to whom the agreement referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) applies,`
  line `shall not be entitled to claim any relief under such agreement unless 3 [a certificate of his being a resident]`
  line `in any specified territory outside India, is obtained by him from the Government of that specified`
  line territory.]
  line `4 [( 5 ) The assessee referred to in sub-section ( 4 ) shall also provide such other documents and`
  line `information, as may be prescribed.]`
  line `Explanation 1. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the charge of tax in respect of a`
  line `company incorporated in the specified territory outside India at a rate higher than the rate at which a`
  line `domestic company is chargeable, shall not be regarded as less favourable charge or levy of tax in respect`
  line `of such company.`
  line `Explanation 2. — For the purposes of this section, the expressions —`
  line `( a ) “specified association” me ans any institution, association or body, whether incorporated or`
  line `not, functioning under any law for the time being in force in India or the laws of the specified`
  line `territory outside India and which may be notified as such by the Central Government for the purposes`
  line `of this section;`
  line `( b ) “specified territory” means any area outside India which may be notified as such by the`
  line `Central Government for the purposes of this section.`
  line `5 [ Explanation 3. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that where any term is used in any`
  line `agreement entered into under sub-section ( 1 ) and not defined under the said agreement or the Act, but is`
  line `assigned a meaning to it in the notification issued under sub-section ( 3 ) and the notification issued`
  line `thereunder being in force, then, the meaning assigned to such term shall be deemed to have effect from`
  line `the date on which the said agreement came into force.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016). Earlier sub-section ( 2A ) was inserted by Act 23 of 2012, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-4-`
  line `2013) and later omitted by Act 17 of 2013, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 24, for “a certificate, containing such particulars as may be prescribed, of his being a resident”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 24, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-6-2006).`
