  content obj_root_law_sections_439_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_439_footnotes
  sourcePage 439
obj_root_law_sections_439_content:
  string
  line 439
  line `1 [ Explanation 4. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that where any term used in an`
  line `agreement entered into under sub-section ( 1 ) is defined under the said agreement, the said term shall have`
  line `the same meaning as assigned to it in the agreement; and where the term is not defined in the said`
  line `agreement, but defined in the Act, it shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in the Act and`
  line `explanation, if any, given to it by the Central Government.]`
  line `91. Countries with which no agreement exists. — ( 1 ) If any person who is resident in India in any`
  line `previous year proves that, in respect of his income which accrued or arose during that previous year`
  line `outside India (and which is not deemed to accrue or arise in India), he has paid in any country with which`
  line `there is no agreement under section 90 for the relief or avoidance of double taxation, income-tax, by`
  line `deduction or otherwise, under the law in force in that country, he shall be entitled to the deduction from`
  line `the Indian income-tax payable by him of a sum calculated on such doubly taxed income at the Indian rate`
  line `of tax or the rate of tax of the said country, whichever is the lower, or at the Indian rate of tax if both the`
  line `rates are equal.`
  line `( 2 ) If any person who is resident in India in any previous year proves that in respect of his income`
  line `which accrued or arose to him during that previous year in Pakistan he has paid in that country, by`
  line `deduction or otherwise, tax payable to the Government under any law for the time being in force in that`
  line `country relating to taxation of agricultural income, he shall be entitled to a deduction from the Indian`
  line `income-tax payable by him —`
  line `( a ) of the amount of the tax paid in Pakistan under any law aforesaid on such income which is`
  line `liable to tax under this Act also; or`
  line `( b ) of a sum calculated on that income at the Indian rate of tax;`
  line `whichever is less.`
  line `( 3 ) If any non-resident person is assessed on his share in the income of a registered firm assessed as`
  line `resident in India in any previous year and such share includes any income accruing or arising outside`
  line `India during that previous year (and which is not deemed to accrue or arise in India) in a country with`
  line `which there is no agreement under section 90 for the relief or avoidance of double taxation and he proves`
  line `that he has paid income-tax by deduction or otherwise under the law in force in that country in respect of`
  line `the income so included he shall be entitled to a deduction from the Indian income-tax payable by him of a`
  line `sum calculated on such doubly taxed income so included at the Indian rate of tax or the rate of tax of the`
  line `said country, whichever is the lower, or at the Indian rate of tax if both the rates are equal.`
  line `Explanation. — In this section, —`
  line `( i ) the expression “Indian income - tax” means income -tax 2 *** charged in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act;`
  line `( ii ) the expression “Indian rate of tax” means the rate determined by dividing the amount of`
  line `Indian income-tax after deduction of any relief due under the provisions of this Act but before`
  line `deduction of 3 [any relief due under this Chapter], by the total income;`
  line `( iii ) the expression “rate of tax of the said country” means income -tax and super-tax actually paid`
  line `in the said country in accordance with the corresponding laws in force in the said country after`
  line `deduction of all relief due, but before deduction of any relief due in the said country in respect of`
  line `double taxation, divided by the whole amount of the income as assessed in the said country;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `2. The words “and super - tax” omitted by Act 10 of 1965, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 5 of 1964, s. 20, for “any relief due under this section” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1964).`
