  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_440_footnotes
  sourcePage 440
obj_root_law_sections_440_content:
  string
  line 440
  line `( iv ) the expression “income - tax” in relation to any country includes any excess profits tax or`
  line `business profits tax charged on the profits by the Government of any part of that country or a local`
  line `authority in that country.`
  line `CHAPTER X`
  line `S PECIAL PROVISIONS RELATING TO AVOIDANCE OF TAX`
  line `1 [ 92. Computation of income from international transaction having regard to arm’s length`
  line `price. — ( 1 ) Any income arising from an international transaction shall be computed having regard to the`
  line `arm’s length price.`
  line `Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that the allowance for any expense or`
  line `interest arising from an international transaction shall also be determined having regard to the arm’s`
  line `length price.`
  line `( 2 ) Where in an 2 [international transaction or specified domestic transaction], two or more associated`
  line `enterprises enter into a mutual agreement or arrangement for the allocation or apportionment of, or any`
  line `contribution to, any cost or expense incurred or to be incurred in connection with a benefit, service or`
  line `facility provided or to be provided to any one or more of such enterprises, the cost or expense allocated or`
  line `apportioned to, or, as the case may be, contributed by, any such enterprise shall be determined having`
  line `regard to the arm ’ s length price of such benefit, service or facility, as the case may be.`
  line `3 [( 2A ) Any allowance for an expenditure or interest or allocation of any cost or expense or any`
  line `income in relation to the specified domestic transaction shall be compu ted having regard to the arm’s`
  line `length price.]`
  line `( 3 ) The provisions of this section shall not apply in a case where the computation of income`
  line `under 4 [sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2A )] or the determination of the allowance for any expense or`
  line `interest under 5 [sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2A )], or the determination of any cost or expense allocated`
  line `or apportioned, or, as the case may be, contributed under sub-section ( 2 ) 3 [or sub-section ( 2A )], has the`
  line `effect of reducing the income chargeable to tax or increasing the loss, as the case may be, computed on`
  line `the basis of entries made in the books of account in respect of the previous year in which the`
  line `2 [international transaction or specified domestic transaction] was entered into.]`
  line `92A. Meaning of associated enterprise. — ( 1 ) For the purposes of this section andsections`
  line `92, 92B, 92C, 92D, 92E and 92F, “associated enterprise”, in relation to another enterprise, means an`
  line `enterprise —`
  line `( a ) which participates, directly or indirectly, or through one or more intermediaries, in the`
  line `management or control or capital of the other enterprise; or`
  line `( b ) in respect of which one or more persons who participate, directly or indirectly, or through one`
  line `or more intermediaries, in its management or control or capital, are the same persons who participate,`
  line `directly or indirectly, or through one or more intermediaries, in the management or control or capital`
  line `of the other enterprise.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 39, for section 92 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).earlier subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 49 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 34, for “international transaction” (we.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 34, ibid. (we.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 34, ibid., for “sub -section ( 1 )” (we.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 34, ibid., for “that sub - section” (we.f. 1 -4-2013).`
