obj_root_law_sections_441:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-441
  sectionNo (441)
  orderNo 441
  title `Page 441`
  content obj_root_law_sections_441_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_441_footnotes
  sourcePage 441
obj_root_law_sections_441_content:
  string
  line 441
  line `1 [( 2 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), two enterprises shall be deemed to be associated enterprises`
  line `if, at any time during the previous year, — ]`
  line `( a ) one enterprise holds, directly or indirectly, shares carrying not less than twenty-six per cent.`
  line `of the voting power in the other enterprise; or`
  line `( b ) any person or enterprise holds, directly or indirectly, shares carrying not less than twenty-six`
  line `per cent. of the voting power in each of such enterprises; or`
  line `( c ) a loan advanced by one enterprise to the other enterprise constitutes not less than fifty-one per`
  line `cent of the book value of the total assets of the other enterprise; or`
  line `( d ) one enterprise guarantees not less than ten per cent. of the total borrowings of the other`
  line `enterprise; or`
  line `( e ) more than half of the board of directors or members of the governing board, or one or more`
  line `executive directors or executive members of the governing board of one enterprise, are appointed by`
  line `the other enterprise; or`
  line `( f ) more than half of the directors or members of the governing board, or one or more of the`
  line `executive directors or members of the governing board, of each of the two enterprises are appointed`
  line `by the same person or persons; or`
  line `( g ) the manufacture or processing of goods or articles or business carried out by one enterprise is`
  line `wholly dependent on the use of know-how, patents, copyrights, trade-marks, licences, franchises or`
  line `any other business or commercial rights of similar nature, or any data, documentation, drawing or`
  line `specification relating to any patent, invention, model, design, secret formula or process, of which the`
  line `other enterprise is the owner or in respect of which the other enterprise has exclusive rights; or`
  line `( h ) ninety per cent or more of the raw materials and consumables required for the manufacture or`
  line `processing of goods or articles carried out by one enterprise, are supplied by the other enterprise, or`
  line `by persons specified by the other enterprise, and the prices and other conditions relating to the supply`
  line `are influenced by such other enterprise; or`
  line `( i ) the goods or articles manufactured or processed by one enterprise, are sold to the other`
  line `enterprise or to persons specified by the other enterprise, and the prices and other conditions relating`
  line `thereto are influenced by such other enterprise; or`
  line `( j ) where one enterprise is controlled by an individual, the other enterprise is also controlled by`
  line `such individual or his relative or jointly by such individual and relative of such individual; or`
  line `( k ) where one enterprise is controlled by a Hindu undivided family, the other enterprise is`
  line `controlled by a member of such Hindu undivided family or by a relative of a member of such Hindu`
  line `undivided family or jointly by such member and his relative; or`
  line `( l ) where one enterprise is a firm, association of persons or body of individuals, the other`
  line `enterprise holds not less than ten per cent interest in such firm, association of persons or body of`
  line `individuals; or`
  line `( m ) there exists between the two enterprises, any relationship of mutual interest, as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 40, f or “( 2 ) Two enterprises shall be deemed to be associated enterprises, if, at any time`
  line `during the previous year, —” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2002).`
