  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_442_footnotes
  sourcePage 442
obj_root_law_sections_442_content:
  string
  line 442
  line `92B. Meaning of international transaction. — ( 1 ) For the purposes of this section and`
  line `sections 92, 92C, 92D and 92E, “international transaction” means a transaction between two or more`
  line `associated enterprises, either or both of whom are non-residents, in the nature of purchase, sale or lease of`
  line `tangible or intangible property, or provision of services, or lending or borrowing money, or any other`
  line `transaction having a bearing on the profits, income, losses or assets of such enterprises, and shall include`
  line `a mutual agreement or arrangement between two or more associated enterprises for the allocation or`
  line `apportionment of, or any contribution to, any cost or expense incurred or to be incurred in connection`
  line `with a benefit, service or facility provided or to be provided to any one or more of such enterprises.`
  line `( 2 ) A transaction entered into by an enterprise with a person other than an associated enterprise shall,`
  line `for the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), be 1 [deemed to be an international transaction] entered into between`
  line `two associated enterprises, if there exists a prior agreement in relation to the relevant transaction between`
  line `such other person and the associated enterprise, or the terms of the relevant transaction are determined in`
  line `substance between such other person and the associated enterprise 2 [where the enterprise or the associated`
  line `enterprise or both of them are non-residents irrespective of whether such other person is a non-resident or`
  line not].
  line `3 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that —`
  line `( i ) the expression “international transaction” shall include —`
  line `( a ) the purchase, sale, transfer, lease or use of tangible property including building,`
  line `transportation vehicle, machinery, equipment, tools, plant, furniture, commodity or any other`
  line `article, product or thing;`
  line `( b ) the purchase, sale, transfer, lease or use of intangible property, including the transfer of`
  line `ownership or the provision of use of rights regarding land use, copyrights, patents, trademarks,`
  line `licences, franchises, customer list, marketing channel, brand, commercial secret, know-how,`
  line `industrial property right, exterior design or practical and new design or any other business or`
  line `commercial rights of similar nature;`
  line `( c ) capital financing, including any type of long-term or short-term borrowing, lending or`
  line `guarantee, purchase or sale of marketable securities or any type of advance, payments or deferred`
  line `payment or receivable or any other debt arising during the course of business;`
  line `( d ) provision of services, including provision of market research, market development,`
  line `marketing management, administration, technical service, repairs, design, consultation, agency,`
  line `scientific research, legal or accounting service;`
  line `( e ) a transaction of business restructuring or reorganisation, entered into by an enterprise`
  line `with an associated enterprise, irrespective of the fact that it has bearing on the profit, income,`
  line `losses or assets of such enterprises at the time of the transaction or at any future date;`
  line `( ii ) the expression “intangible property” shall include—`
  line `( a ) marketing related intangible assets, such as, trademarks, trade names, brand names, logos;`
  line `( b ) technology related intangible assets, such as, process patents, patent applications,`
  line `technical documentation such as laboratory notebooks, technical know-how;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 31, for “deemed to be a transaction” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2015).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 31, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_442_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_443:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-443
  sectionNo (443)
  orderNo 443
  title `Page 443`
  content obj_root_law_sections_443_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_443_footnotes
  sourcePage 443
obj_root_law_sections_443_content:
  string
  line 443
  line `( c ) artistic related intangible assets, such as, literary works and copyrights, musical`
  line `compositions, copyrights, maps, engravings;`
  line `( d ) data processing related intangible assets, such as, proprietary computer software, software`
  line `copyrights, automated databases, and integrated circuit masks and masters;`
  line `( e ) engineering related intangible assets, such as, industrial design, product patents, trade`
  line `secrets, engineering drawing and schematics, blueprints, proprietary documentation;`
  line `( f ) customer related intangible assets, such as, customer lists, customer contracts, customer`
  line `relationship, open purchase orders;`
  line `( g ) contract related intangible assets, such as, favourable supplier, contracts, licence`
  line `agreements, franchise agreements, non-compete agreements;`
  line `( h ) human capital related intangible assets, such as, trained and organised work force,`
  line `employment agreements, union contracts;`
  line `( i ) location related intangible assets, such as, leasehold interest, mineral exploitation rights,`
  line `easements, air rights, water rights;`
  line `( j ) goodwill related intangible assets, such as, institutional goodwill, professional practice`
  line `goodwill, personal goodwill of professional, celebrity goodwill, general business going concern`
  line value;
  line `( k ) methods, programmes, systems, procedures, campaigns, surveys, studies, forecasts,`
  line `estimates, customer lists, or technical data;`
  line `( l ) any other similar item that derives its value from its intellectual content rather than its`
  line `physical attributes.]`
  line `1 [ 92BA. Meaning of specified domestic transaction. — For the purposes of this section and`
  line `sections 92, 92C, 92D and 92E, “specified domestic transaction” in case of an assessee means any of the`
  line `following transactions, not being an international transaction, namely: —`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `( ii ) any transaction referred to in section 80A;`
  line `( iii ) any transfer of goods or services referred to in sub-section ( 8 ) of section 80-IA;`
  line `( iv ) any business transacted between the assessee and other person as referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 10 ) of section 80-IA;`
  line `( v ) any transaction, referred to in any other section under Chapter VI-A or section 10AA, to`
  line `which provisions of sub-section ( 8 ) or sub-section ( 10 ) of section 80-IA are applicable; or`
  line `( vi ) any other transaction as may be prescribed,`
  line `and where the aggregate of such transactions entered into by the assessee in the previous year exceeds a`
  line `sum of 3 [twentycrore rupees].]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `2. Clause ( i ) omitted by Act 7 of 2017, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 25, for “five crore rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_443_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_444:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-444
  sectionNo (444)
  orderNo 444
  title `Page 444`
  content obj_root_law_sections_444_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_444_footnotes
  sourcePage 444
obj_root_law_sections_444_content:
  string
  line 444
  line `92C. Computation of arm’s length price. — ( 1 ) The arm’s length price in relation to an`
  line `1 [international transaction or specified domestic transaction] shall be determined by any of the following`
  line `methods, being the most appropriate method, having regard to the nature of transaction or class of`
  line `transaction or class of associated persons or functions performed by such persons or such other relevant`
  line `factors as the Board may prescribe, namely: —`
  line `( a ) comparable uncontrolled price method;`
  line `( b ) resale price method;`
  line `( c ) cost plus method;`
  line `( d ) profit split method;`
  line `( e ) transactional net margin method;`
  line `( f ) such other method as may be prescribed by the Board.`
  line `( 2 ) The most appropriate method referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be applied, for determination of`
  line `arm’s length price, in the manner as may be prescribed:`
  line `2 [Provided that where more than one price is determined by the most appropriate method, the arm ’ s`
  line `length price shall be taken to be the arithmetical mean of such prices:`
  line `Provided further that i f the variation between the arm’ s length price so determined and price at which`
  line `the 1 [international transaction or specified domestic transaction] has actually been undertaken does not`
  line `exceed 3 [such percentage 4 [not exceeding three per cent.] of the latter], as may be notified] by the Central`
  line `Government in the Official Gazette in this behalf, the price at which the 1 [international transaction or`
  line `specified domestic transaction] has actually been undertaken shall be deemed to be the arm’s length`
  line `price:]`
  line `5 [Provided also that where more than one price is determined by the most appropriate method, the`
  line `arm’s length price in relation to an in ternational transaction or specified domestic transaction undertaken`
  line `on or after the 1st day of April, 2014, shall be computed in such manner as may be prescribed and`
  line `accordingly the first and second proviso shall not apply.]`
  line `6 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that the provisions of the second`
  line `proviso shall also be applicable to all assessment or reassessment proceedings pending before an`
  line `Assessing Officer as on the 1st day of October, 2009.]`
  line `7 [( 2A ) Where the first proviso to sub-section ( 2 ) as it stood before its amendment by the Finance (No.`
  line `2) Act, 2009 (33 of 2009), is applicable in respect of an international transaction for an assessment year`
  line `and the variation between the arithmetical mean referred to in the said proviso and the price at which such`
  line `transaction has actually been undertaken exceeds five per cent of the arithmetical mean, then, the assessee`
  line `shall not be entitled to exercise the option as referred to in the said proviso.]`
  line `8 [( 2B ) Nothing contained in sub-section ( 2A ) shall empower the Assessing Officer either to assess or`
  line `reassess under section 147 or pass an order enhancing the assessment or reducing a refund already made`
  line `or otherwise increasing the liability of the assessee under section 154 for any assessment year the`
  line `proceedings of which have been completed before the 1st day of October, 2009.]`
  line `( 3 ) Where during the course of any proceeding for the assessment of income, the Assessing Officer is,`
  line `on the basis of material or information or document in his possession, of the opinion that —`
  line `( a ) the price charged or paid in an 1 [internationaltransaction or specified domestic transaction]`
  line `has not been determined in accordance with sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ); or`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 38, for “international transaction” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-10-2009). Earlier substituted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 41, for proviso (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 13, for “five per cent. of the latter” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2012).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 37, for “does not exceed such percentage of latter as may be notified” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013)`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 37 (w.r.e.f. 1-10-2009).`
  line `7. Ins. by s. 37, ibid. (w.r.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 37 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
