obj_root_law_sections_445_content:
  string
  line 445
  line `( b ) any information and document relating to an 1 [internationaltransaction or specified domestic`
  line `transaction] have not been kept and maintained by the assessee in accordance with the provisions`
  line `contained in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 92D and the rules made in this behalf; or`
  line `( c ) the information or data used in computation of the arm's length price is not reliable or correct;`
  line or
  line `( d ) the assessee has failed to furnish, within the specified time, any information or document`
  line `which he was required to furnish by a notice issued under sub-section ( 3 ) of section 92D,`
  line `the Assessing Officer may proceed to determine the arm's length price in relation to the said`
  line `1 [internationaltransaction or specified domestic transaction] in accordance with sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ),`
  line `on the basis of such material or information or document available with him:`
  line `Provided that an opportunity shall be given by the Assessing Officer by serving a notice calling upon`
  line `the assessee to show cause, on a date and time to be specified in the notice, why the arm's length price`
  line `should not be so determined on the basis of material or information or document in the possession of the`
  line `Assessing Officer.`
  line `( 4 ) Where an arm ’ s length price is determined by the Assessing Officer under sub-section ( 3 ), the`
  line `Assessing Officer may compute the total income of the assessee having regard to the arm's length price so`
  line `determined:`
  line `Provided that no deduction under section 10A or 2 [section 10AA] or section 10B or under`
  line `Chapter VI-A shall be allowed in respect of the amount of income by which the total income of the`
  line `assessee is enhanced after computation of income under this sub-section:`
  line `Provided further that where the total income of an associated enterprise is computed under this`
  line `sub- section on determination of the arm’s length price paid to anothe r associated enterprise from which`
  line `tax has been deducted 3 [or was deductible] under the provisions of Chapter XVIIB, the income of the`
  line `other associated enterprise shall not be recomputed by reason of such determination of arm's length price`
  line `in the case of the first mentioned enterprise.`
  line `4 [92CA.Reference to Transfer Pricing Officer. — ( 1 ) Where any person, being the assessee, has`
  line `entered into an 1 [international transaction or specified domestic] transaction in any previous year, and the`
  line `Assessing Officer considers it necessary or expedient so to do, he may, with the previous approval of`
  line `the 5 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner], refer the computation of the arm’s length price in`
  line `relation to the said 1 [international transaction or specified domestic] transaction under section 92C to the`
  line `Transfer Pricing Officer.`
  line `( 2 ) Where a reference is made under sub-section ( 1 ), the Transfer Pricing Officer shall serve a notice`
  line `on the assessee requiring him to produce or cause to be produced on a date to be specified therein, any`
  line `evidence on which the assessee may rely in support of the computation made by him of the arm ’ s length`
  line `price in relation to the 1 [international transaction or specified domestic] transaction referred to in sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ).`
  line `6 [( 2A ) Where any other international transaction [other than an international transaction referred`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ),] comes to the notice of the Transfer Pricing Officer during the course of the`
  line `proceedings before him, the provisions of this Chapter shall apply as if such other international`
  line `transaction is an international transaction referred to him under sub-section ( 1 ).]`
  line `7 [( 2B ) Where in respect of an international transaction, the assessee has not furnished the report`
  line `under section 92E and such transaction comes to the notice of the Transfer Pricing Officer during the`
  line `course of the proceeding before him, the provisions of this Chapter shall apply as if such transaction is an`
  line `international transaction referred to him under sub-section ( 1 ).]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 38, for “international transaction” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 21, for “section 10A or section 10M or section 10B” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2007).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 42, ibid. (1-6-2012).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-6-2011).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 39 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
