  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_446_footnotes
  sourcePage 446
obj_root_law_sections_446_content:
  string
  line 446
  line `1 [( 2C ) Nothing contained in sub-section ( 2B ) shall empower the Assessing Officer either to assess or`
  line `reassess under section 147 or pass an order enhancing the assessment or reducing a refund already made`
  line `or otherwise increasing the liability of the assessee under section 154, for any assessment year,`
  line `proceedings for which have been completed before the 1st day of July, 2012.]`
  line `( 3 ) On the date specified in the notice under sub-section ( 2 ), or as soon thereafter as may be, after`
  line `hearing such evidence as the assessee may produce, including any information or documents referred to`
  line `in sub-section ( 3 ) of section 92D and after considering such evidence as the Transfer Pricing Officer may`
  line `require on any specified points and after taking into account all relevant materials which he has gathered,`
  line `the Transfer Pricing Officer shall, by order in writing, determine the arm's length price in relation to the`
  line `2 [internationaltransaction or specified domestic] transaction in accordance with sub-section ( 3 ) of section`
  line `92C and send a copy of his order to the Assessing Officer and to the assessee.`
  line `3 [( 3A ) Wherea reference was made under sub-section ( 1 ) before the 1st day of June, 2007 but the`
  line `order under sub-section ( 3 ) has not been made by the Transfer Pricing Officer before the said date, or a`
  line `reference under sub-section ( 1 ) is made on or after the 1st day of June, 2007, an order under sub-section`
  line `( 3 ) may be made at any time before sixty days prior to the date on which the period of limitation referred`
  line `to in section 153, or as the case may be, in section 153B for making the order of assessment or`
  line `reassessment or recomputation or fresh assessment, as the case may be, expires:]`
  line `4 [Provided that in the circumstances referred to in clause ( ii ) or clause ( x ) of Explanation 1 to section`
  line `153, if the period of limitation available to the Transfer Pricing Officer for making an order is less than`
  line `sixty days, such remaining period shall be extended to sixty days and the aforesaid period of limitation`
  line `shall be deemed to have been extended accordingly. ]`
  line `3 [( 4 ) On receipt of the order under sub-section ( 3 ), the Assessing Officer shall proceed to compute the`
  line `total income of the assessee under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 92C in conformity with the arm ’ s length`
  line `price as so determined by the Transfer Pricing Officer.]`
  line `( 5 ) With a view to rectifying any mistake apparent from the record, the Transfer Pricing Officer may`
  line `amend any order passed by him under sub-section ( 3 ), and the provisions of section 154 shall, so far as`
  line `may be, apply accordingly.`
  line `( 6 ) Where any amendment is made by the Transfer Pricing Officer under sub-section ( 5 ), he shall`
  line `send a copy of his order to the Assessing Officer who shall thereafter proceed to amend the order of`
  line `assessment in conformity with such order of the Transfer Pricing Officer.`
  line `( 7 ) T he Transfer Pricing Officer may, for the purposes of determining the arm’s length price under`
  line `this section, exercise all or any of the powers specified in clauses ( a ) to ( d ) of sub-section ( 1 ) ofsection`
  line `131 or sub-section ( 6 ) of section 133 5 [or section 133A].`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, “Transfer Pricing Officer” means a Joint`
  line `Commissioner or Deputy Commissioner or Assistant Commissioner authorised by the Board to perform`
  line `all or any of the functions of an Assessing Officer specified in section 92C and 92D in respect of any`
  line `person or class of persons.]`
  line `6 [92CB.Power of Board to make safe harbour rules. — ( 1 ) The determination of arm ’ s length price`
  line `under section 92C or section 92CA shall be subject to safe harbour rules.`
  line `( 2 ) The Board may, for the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), make rules for safe harbour.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, “safe harbour” means circumstances in which the`
  line `income-tax authorities shall accept the transfer price declared by the assessee.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 39 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 38, ibid., for “international transaction” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-6-2011).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
