  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_447_footnotes
  sourcePage 447
obj_root_law_sections_447_content:
  string
  line 447
  line `1 [ 92CC. Advance pricing agreement. — ( 1 ) The Board, with the approval of the Central`
  line `Government, may enter into an advance pricing agreement with any person, determining the arm’s length`
  line `price or specifying the manner in which arm’s length price is to be determined, in relation to an`
  line `international transaction to be entered into by that person.`
  line `( 2 ) The manner of determination of arm’s length price referred to in sub -section ( 1 ), may include the`
  line `methods referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 92C or any other method, with such adjustments or`
  line `variations, as may be necessary or expedient so to do.`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 92C or section 92CA, the arm ’ s length price of any`
  line `international transaction, in respect of which the advance pricing agreement has been entered into, shall`
  line `be determined in accordance with the advance pricing agreement so entered.`
  line `( 4 ) The agreement referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be valid for such period not exceeding five`
  line `consecutive previous years as may be specified in the agreement.`
  line `( 5 ) The advance pricing agreement entered into shall be binding —`
  line `( a ) on the person in whose case, and in respect of the transaction in relation to which, the`
  line `agreement has been entered into; and`
  line `( b ) on the 2 [Principal Commissioner or] Commissioner, and the income-tax authorities`
  line `subordinate to him, in respect of the said person and the said transaction.`
  line `( 6 ) The agreement referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall not be binding if there is a change in law or`
  line `facts having bearing on the agreement so entered.`
  line `( 7 ) The Board may, with the approval of the Central Government, by an order, declare an agreement`
  line `to be void abinitio, if it finds that the agreement has been obtained by the person by fraud or`
  line `misrepresentation of facts.`
  line `( 8 ) Upon declaring the agreement void ab initio, —`
  line `( a ) all the provisions of the Act shall apply to the person as if such agreement had never been`
  line `entered into; and`
  line `( b ) notwithstanding anything contained in the Act, for the purpose of computing any period of`
  line `limitation under this Act, the period beginning with the date of such agreement and ending on the date`
  line `of order under sub-section ( 7 ) shall be excluded:`
  line `Provided that where immediately after the exclusion of the aforesaid period, the period of`
  line `limitation, referred to in any provision of this Act, is less than sixty days, such remaining period shall`
  line `be extended to sixty days and the aforesaid period of limitation shall be deemed to be extended`
  line accordingly.
  line `( 9 ) The Board may, for the purposes of this section, prescribe a scheme specifying therein the`
  line `manner, form, procedure and any other matter generally in respect of the advance pricing agreement.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_447_footnotes:
