obj_root_law_sections_448_content:
  string
  line 448
  line `1 [( 9A ) The agreement referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), may, subject to such conditions, procedure and`
  line `manner as may be prescribed, provide for determining the arm ’ s length price or specify the manner in`
  line `which arm’s length price shall be determined in relation to the international transaction entered into by`
  line `the person during any period not exceeding four previous years preceding the first of the previous years`
  line `referred to in sub-section ( 4 ), and the arm’s length price of such international transaction shall be`
  line `determined in accordance with the said agreement.]`
  line `( 10 ) Where an application is made by a person for entering into an agreement referred to in sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ), the proceeding shall be deemed to be pending in the case of the person for the purposes of the`
  line Act.
  line `92CD. Effect to advance pricing agreement. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary`
  line `contained in section 139, where any person has entered into an agreement and prior to the date of entering`
  line `into the agreement, any return of income has been furnished under the provisions of section 139 for any`
  line `assessment year relevant to a previous year to which such agreement applies, such person shall furnish,`
  line `within a period of three months from the end of the month in which the said agreement was entered into, a`
  line `modified return in accordance with and limited to the agreement.`
  line `( 2 ) Save as otherwise provided in this section, all other provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly`
  line `as if the modified return is a return furnished under section 139.`
  line `( 3 ) If the assessment or reassessment proceedings for an assessment year relevant to a previous year`
  line `to which the agreement applies have been completed before the expiry of period allowed for furnishing of`
  line `modified return under sub-section ( 1 ), the Assessing Officer shall, in a case where modified return is filed`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ), proceed to assess or reassess or recompute the total`
  line `income of the relevant assessment year having regard to and in accordance with the agreement.`
  line `( 4 ) Where the assessment or reassessment proceedings for an assessment year relevant to the previous`
  line `year to which the agreement applies are pending on the date of filing of modified return in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ), the Assessing Officer shall proceed to complete the assessment or`
  line `reassessment proceedings in accordance with the agreement taking into consideration the modified return`
  line `so furnished.`
  line `( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 153 or section 153B or section 144C, —`
  line `( a ) the order of assessment, reassessment or recomputation of total income under sub-section ( 3 )`
  line `shall be passed within a period of one year from the end of the financial year in which the modified`
  line `return under sub-section ( 1 ) is furnished;`
  line `( b ) the period of limitation as provided in section 153 or section 153B or section 144C for`
  line `completion of pending assessment or reassessment proceedings referred to in sub-section ( 4 ) shall be`
  line `extended by a period of twelve months.`
  line `( 6 ) For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “agreement” means an agreement referred to in sub -section ( 1 ) of section 92CC;`
  line `( ii ) the assessment or reassessment proceedings for an assessment year shall be deemed to have`
  line `been completed where —`
  line `( a ) an assessment or reassessment order has been passed; or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
