obj_root_law_sections_449_content:
  string
  line 449
  line `( b ) no notice has been issued under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 143 till the expiry of the`
  line `limitation period provided under the said section.]`
  line `1 [ 92CE. Secondary adjustment in certain cases. — ( 1 ) Where a primary adjustment to transfer`
  line `price, —`
  line `( i ) has been made suomotu by the assessee in his return of income;`
  line `( ii ) made by the Assessing Officer has been accepted by the assessee;`
  line `( iii ) is determined by an advance pricing agreement entered into by the assessee under section`
  line 92CC;
  line `( iv ) is made as per the safe harbour rules framed under section 92CB; or`
  line `( v ) is arising as a result of resolution of an assessment by way of the mutual agreement procedure`
  line `under an agreement entered into under section 90 or section 90A for avoidance of double taxation,`
  line `the assessee shall make a secondary adjustment:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall apply, if, —`
  line `( i ) the amount of primary adjustment made in any previous year does not exceed one crore`
  line `rupees; and`
  line `( ii ) the primary adjustment is made in respect of an assessment year commencing on or before the`
  line `1st day of April, 2016.`
  line `( 2 ) Where, as a result of primary adjustment to the transfer price, there is an increase in the total`
  line `income or reduction in the loss, as the case may be, of the assessee, the excess money which is available`
  line `with its associated enterprise, if not repatriated to India within the time as may be prescribed, shall be`
  line `deemed to be an advance made by the assessee to such associated enterprise and the interest on such`
  line `advance, shall be computed in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 3 ) For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “associated enterprise” shall have the meaning assigned to it in sub -section ( 1 ) and`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 92A;`
  line `( ii ) “arm’s length price” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( ii ) of section 92F;`
  line `( iii ) “excess money” means the difference between the arm’s length price determined in primary`
  line `adjustment and the price at which the international transaction has actually been undertaken;`
  line `( iv ) “primary adjustment” to a transfer price, means the determination of transfer price in`
  line `accordance with the arm’s length principle resulting in an increase in the total income or reduction in`
  line `the loss, as the case may be, of the assessee;`
  line `( v ) “secondary adjustment” means an adjustment in the books of account of the assessee and its`
  line `associated enterprise to reflect that the actual allocation of profits between the assessee and its`
  line `associated enterprise are consistent with the transfer price determined as a result of primary`
  line `adjustment, thereby removing the imbalance between cash account and actual profit of the assessee.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_449_footnotes:
  string
