obj_root_law_sections_450_content:
  string
  line 450
  line `92D. Maintenance and keeping of information and document by persons entering into an`
  line `1 [ international transaction or specified domestic transaction]. — ( 1 ) Every person who has entered into`
  line `an 1 [international transaction or specified domestic transaction] shall keep and maintain such information`
  line `and document in respect thereof, as may be prescribed.`
  line `2 [Provided thatthe person, being a constituent entity of an international group, shall also keep and`
  line `maintain such information and document in respect of an international group as may be prescribed.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( A ) “constituent entity” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( d ) of sub-section ( 9 )`
  line `of section 286;`
  line `( B ) “international group” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( g ) of sub-section ( 9 )`
  line `of section 286.]`
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section ( 1 ), the Board may prescribe the`
  line `period for which the information and document shall be kept and maintained under that sub-section.`
  line `( 3 ) The Assessing Officer or the Commissioner (Appeals) may, in the course of any proceeding under`
  line `this Act, require any person who has entered into an 1 [international transaction or specified domestic`
  line `transaction] to furnish any information or document in respect thereof, as may be prescribed under sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ), within a period of thirty days from the date of receipt of a notice issued in this regard:`
  line `Provided that the Assessing Officer or the Commissioner (Appeals) may, on an application made by`
  line `such person, extend the period of thirty days by a further period not exceeding thirty days.`
  line `2 [( 4 ) Withoutprejudice to the provisions of sub-section ( 3 ), the person referred to in the proviso to`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) shall furnish the information and document referred to in the said proviso to the authority`
  line `prescribed under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 286, in such manner, on or before the date, as may be`
  line prescribed.]
  line `92E.Report from an accountant to be furnished by persons entering into 1 [international`
  line `transaction or specified domestic transaction]. — Every person who has entered into`
  line `an 1 [internationaltransaction or specified domestic transaction] during a previous year shall obtain a report`
  line `from an accountant and furnish such report on or before the specified date in the prescribed form duly`
  line `signed and verified in the prescribed manner by such accountant and setting forth such particulars as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line `92F.Definitions of certain terms relevant to computation of arm’s length price, et c. — In section`
  line `92, 92A, 92B, 92C, 92D and 92E, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( i ) “accountant” shall have the same meaning as in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 288;`
  line `( ii ) “arm’s length price” means a price which is applied or propo sed to be applied in a transaction`
  line `between persons other than associated enterprises, in uncontrolled conditions;`
  line `( iii ) “enterprise” means a person (including a permanent establishment of such person) who is, or`
  line `has been, or is proposed to be, engaged in any activity, relating to the production, storage, supply,`
  line `distribution, acquisition or control of articles or goods, or know-how, patents, copyrights, trade-`
  line `marks, licences, franchises or any other business or commercial rights of similar nature, or any data,`
  line `documentation, drawing or specification relating to any patent, invention, model, design, secret`
  line `formula or process, of which the other enterprise is the owner or in respect of which the other`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 38, for “international transaction” (w.e.f. 1 -3-2013).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 48 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_450_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_451:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-451
  sectionNo (451)
  orderNo 451
  title `Page 451`
  content obj_root_law_sections_451_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_451_footnotes
  sourcePage 451
obj_root_law_sections_451_content:
  string
  line 451
  line `enterprise has exclusive rights, or the provision of services of any kind, 1 [or in carrying out any work`
  line `in pursuance of a contract,] or in investment, or providing loan or in the business of acquiring,`
  line `holding, underwriting or dealing with shares, debentures or other securities of any other body`
  line `corporate, whether such activity or business is carried on, directly or through one or more of its units`
  line `or divisions or subsidiaries, or whether such unit or division or subsidiary is located at the same place`
  line `where the enterprise is located or at a different place or places;`
  line `1 [( iiia ) “permanent establishment”, referred to in clause ( iii ), includes a fixed place of business`
  line `through which the business of the enterprise is wholly or partly carried on;]`
  line `2 [( iv ) “specified date” shall have the same meaning as assigned to “due date” in Explanation`
  line `2 below sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139;`
  line `( v ) “transaction” includes an arrangement, understanding or action in co ncert, —`
  line `( A ) whether or not such arrangement, understanding or action is formal or in writing; or`
  line `( B ) whether or not such arrangement, understanding or action is intended to be enforceable`
  line `by legal proceeding.]`
  line `93. Avoidance of income-tax by transactions resulting in transfer of income to non-residents. —`
  line `( 1 ) Where there is a transfer of assets by virtue or in consequence whereof, either alone or in conjunction`
  line `with associated operations, any income becomes payable to a non-resident, the following provisions shall`
  line `apply —`
  line `( a ) where any person has, by means of any such transfer, either alone or in conjunction with`
  line `associated operations, acquired any rights by virtue of which he has, within the meaning of this`
  line `section, power to enjoy, whether forthwith or in the future, any income of a non-resident person`
  line `which, if it were income of the first-mentioned person, would be chargeable to income-tax, that`
  line `income shall, whether it would or would not have been chargeable to income-tax apart from the`
  line `provisions of this section, be deemed to be income of the first-mentioned person for all the purposes`
  line `of this Act;`
  line `( b ) where, whether before or after any such transfer, any such first-mentioned person receives or`
  line `is entitled to receive any capital sum the payment whereof is in any way connected with the transfer`
  line `or any associated operations, then any income which, by virtue or in consequence of the transfer,`
  line `either alone or in conjunction with associated operations, has become the income of a non-resident`
  line `shall, whether it would or would not have been chargeable to income-tax apart from the provisions of`
  line `this section, be deemed to be the income of the first-mentioned person for all the purposes of this Act.`
  line `Explanation. — The provisions of this sub-section shall apply also in relation to transfers of assets and`
  line `associated operations carried out before the commencement of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) Where any person has been charged to income-tax on any income deemed to be his under the`
  line `provisions of this section and that income is subsequently received by him, whether as income or in any`
  line `other form, it shall not again be deemed to form part of his income for the purposes of this Act.`
  line `( 3 ) The provisions of this section shall not apply if the first-mentioned person in sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `shows to the satisfaction of the 3 [Assessing Officer] that —`
  line `( a ) neither the transfer nor any associated operation had for its purpose or for one of its purposes`
  line `the avoidance of liability to taxation; or`
  line `( b ) the transfer and all associated operations were bona fide commercial transactions and were`
  line `not designed for the purpose of avoiding liability to taxation.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 43 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 43, ibid., for clause ( iv ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_451_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_452:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-452
  sectionNo (452)
  orderNo 452
  title `Page 452`
  content obj_root_law_sections_452_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_452_footnotes
  sourcePage 452
obj_root_law_sections_452_content:
  string
  line 452
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) references to assets representing any assets, income or accumulations of income include`
  line `references to shares in or obligation of any company to which, or obligation of any other person to`
  line `whom, those assets, that income or those accumulations are or have been transferred;`
  line `( b ) any body corporate incorporated outside India shall be treated as if it were a non-resident;`
  line `( c ) a person shall be deemed to have power to enjoy the income of a non-resident if —`
  line `( i ) the income is in fact so dealt with by any person as to be calculated at some point of time`
  line `and, whether in the form of income or not, to ensure for the benefit of the first-mentioned person`
  line `in sub-section ( 1 ), or`
  line `( ii ) the receipt or accrual of the income operates to increase the value to such first-mentioned`
  line `person of any assets held by him or for his benefit, or`
  line `( iii ) such first-mentioned person receives or is entitled to receive at any time any benefit`
  line `provided or to be provided out of that income or out of moneys which are or will be available for`
  line `the purpose by reason of the effect or successive effects of the associated operations on that`
  line `income and assets which represent that income, or`
  line `( iv ) such first-mentioned person has power by means of the exercise of any power of`
  line `appointment or power of revocation or otherwise to obtain for himself, whether with or without`
  line `the consent of any other person, the beneficial enjoyment of the income, or`
  line `( v ) such first-mentioned person is able, in any manner whatsoever and whether directly or`
  line `indirectly, to control the application of the income;`
  line `( d ) in determining whether a person has power to enjoy income, regard shall be had to the`
  line `substantial result and effect of the transfer and any associated operations, and all benefits which may`
  line `at any time accrue to such person as a result of the transfer and any associated operations shall be`
  line `taken into account irrespective of the nature or form of the benefits.`
  line `( 4 ) ( a ) “Assets” includes property or rights of any kind and “transfer” in relation to rights includes the`
  line `creation of those rights;`
  line `( b ) “associated operation”, in relation to any transfer, means an operation of any kind effected by any`
  line `person in relation to —`
  line `( i ) any of the assets transferred, or`
  line `( ii ) any assets representing, whether directly or indirectly, any of the assets transferred, or`
  line `( iii ) the income arising from any such assets, or`
  line `( iv ) any assets representing, whether directly or indirectly, the accumulations of income arising`
  line `from any such assets;`
  line `( c ) “benefit” includes a payment of any kind;`
  line `( d ) “capital sum” means—`
  line `( i ) any sum paid or payable by way of a loan or repayment of a loan; and`
  line `( ii ) any other sum paid or payable otherwise than as income, being a sum which is not paid or`
  line `payable for full consideration in money or money ’ s worth.`
  line `94. Avoidance of tax by certain transactions in securities. — ( 1 ) Where the owner of any securities`
  line `[in this sub-section and in sub-section ( 2 ) referred to as “the owner”] sells or transfers those securities,`
  line `and buys back or reacquires the securities, then, if the result of the transaction is that any interest`
  line `becoming payable in respect of the securities is receivable otherwise than by the owner, the interest`
  line `payable as aforesaid shall, whether it would or would not have been chargeable to income-tax apart from`
  line `the provisions of this sub-section, be deemed, for all the purposes of this Act, to be the income of the`
  line `owner and not to be the income of any other person.`
obj_root_law_sections_452_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_453:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-453
  sectionNo (453)
  orderNo 453
  title `Page 453`
  content obj_root_law_sections_453_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_453_footnotes
  sourcePage 453
obj_root_law_sections_453_content:
  string
  line 453
  line `Explanation. — The references in this sub-section to buying back or reacquiring the securities shall be`
  line `deemed to include references to buying or acquiring similar securities, so, however, that where similar`
  line `securities are bought or acquired, the owner shall be under no greater liability to income-tax than he`
  line `would have been under if the original securities had been bought back or reacquired.`
  line `( 2 ) Where any person has had at any time during any previous year any beneficial interest in any`
  line `securities, and the result of any transaction relating to such securities or the income thereof is that, in`
  line `respect of such securities within such year, either no income is received by him or the income received by`
  line `him is less than the sum to which the income would have amounted if the income from such securities`
  line `had accrued from day to day and been apportioned accordingly, then the income from such securities for`
  line `such year shall be deemed to be the income of such person.`
  line `( 3 ) The provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) shall not apply if the owner, or the person`
  line `who has had a beneficial interest in the securities, as the case may be, proves to the satisfaction of the`
  line `1 [Assessing Officer] —`
  line `( a ) that there has been no avoidance of income-tax, or`
  line `( b ) that the avoidance of income-tax was exceptional and not systematic and that there was not in`
  line `his case in any of the three preceding years any avoidance of income-tax by a transaction of the`
  line `nature referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ).`
  line `( 4 ) Where any person carrying on a business which consists wholly or partly in dealing in securities,`
  line `buys or acquires any securities and sells back or retransfers the securities, then, if the result of the`
  line `transaction is that interest becoming payable in respect of the securities is receivable by him but is not`
  line `deemed to be his income by reason of the provisions contained in sub-section ( 1 ), no account shall be`
  line `taken of the transaction in computing for any of the purposes of this Act the profits arising from or loss`
  line `sustained in the business.`
  line `( 5 ) Sub-section ( 4 ) shall have effect, subject to any necessary modifications, as if references to selling`
  line `back or retransferring the securities included references to selling or transferring similar securities.`
  line `( 6 ) The 1 [Assessing Officer] may, by notice in writing, require any person to furnish him within such`
  line `time as he may direct (not being less than twenty-eight days), in respect of all securities of which such`
  line `person was the owner or in which he had a beneficial interest at any time during the period specified in`
  line `the notice, such particulars as he considers necessary for the purposes of this section and for the purpose`
  line `of discovering whether income-tax has been borne in respect of the interest on all those securities.`
  line `2 [( 7 ) Where —`
  line `( a ) any person buys or acquires any securities or unit within a period of three months prior to the`
  line `record date;`
  line `3 [( b ) such person sells or transfers —`
  line `( i ) such securities within a period of three months after such date; or`
  line `( ii ) such unit within a period of nine months after such date;]`
  line `( c ) the dividend or income on such securities or unit received or receivable by such person is`
  line exempt,
  line `then, the loss, if any, arising to him on account of such purchase and sale of securities or unit, to the`
  line `extent such loss does not exceed the amount of dividend or income received or receivable on such`
  line `securities or unit, shall be ignored for the purposes of computing his income chargeable to tax.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 25, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
