  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_454_footnotes
  sourcePage 454
obj_root_law_sections_454_content:
  string
  line 454
  line `1 [( 8 ) Where —`
  line `( a ) any person buys or acquires any units within a period of three months prior to the record date;`
  line `( b ) such person is allotted additional units without any payment on the basis of holding of such`
  line `units on such date;`
  line `( c ) such person sells or transfers all or any of the units referred to in clause ( a ) within a period of`
  line `nine months after such date, while continuing to hold all or any of the additional units referred to in`
  line `clause ( b ),`
  line `then, the loss, if any, arising to him on account of such purchase and sale of all or any of such units shall`
  line `be ignored for the purposes of computing his income chargeable to tax and notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other provision of this Act, the amount of loss so ignored shall be deemed to be the cost`
  line `of purchase or acquisition of such additional units referred to in clause ( b ) as are held by him on the date`
  line `of such sale or transfer.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “interest” includes a dividend;`
  line `2 [( aa ) “record date” means such date as may be fixed by—`
  line `( i ) a company for the purposes of entitlement of the holder of the securities to receive`
  line `dividend; or`
  line `( ii ) a Mutual Fund or the Administrator of the specified undertaking or the specified`
  line `company as referred to in the Explanation to clause ( 35 ) of section 10, for the purposes of`
  line `entitlement of the holder of the units to receive income, or additional unit without any`
  line `consideration, as the case may be;`
  line `( b ) “securities” includes stocks and shares;`
  line `( c ) securities shall be deemed to be similar if they entitle their holders to the same rights against`
  line `the same persons as to capital and interest and the same remedies for the enforcement of those rights,`
  line `notwithstanding any difference in the total nominal amounts of the respective securities or in the form`
  line `in which they are held or in the manner in which they can be transferred;`
  line `2 [( d ) “unit” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( b ) of the Explanation to section`
  line 115AB.]
  line `3 [94A. Special measures in respect of transactions with persons located in notified jurisdictional`
  line `area. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may, having regard to the lack of effective exchange of information`
  line `with any country or territory outside India, specify by notification in the Official Gazette such country or`
  line `territory as a notified jurisdictional area in relation to transactions entered into by any assessee.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Act, if an assessee enters into a`
  line `transaction where one of the parties to the transaction is a person located in a notified jurisdictional area,`
  line `then —`
  line `( i ) all the parties to the transaction shall be deemed to be associated enterprises within the`
  line `meaning of section 92A;`
  line `( ii ) any transaction in the nature of purchase, sale or lease of tangible or intangible property or`
  line `provision of service or lending or borrowing money or any other transaction having a bearing on the`
  line `profits, income, losses or assets of the assessee including a mutual agreement or arrangement for`
  line `allocation or apportionment of, or any contribution to, any cost or expense incurred or to be incurred`
  line `in connection with a benefit, service or facility provided or to be provided by or to the assessee shall`
  line `be deemed to be an international transaction within the meaning of section 92B,`
  line `and the provisions of sections 92, 92A, 92B, 92C except the second proviso to sub-section`
  line `( 2 ), 92CA,92CB, 92CD, 92E and 92F shall apply accordingly.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-6-2011).`
obj_root_law_sections_454_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_455:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-455
  sectionNo (455)
  orderNo 455
  title `Page 455`
  content obj_root_law_sections_455_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_455_footnotes
  sourcePage 455
obj_root_law_sections_455_content:
  string
  line 455
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Act, no deduction, —`
  line `( a ) in respect of any payment made to any financial institution located in a notified jurisdictional`
  line `area shall be allowed under this Act, unless the assessee furnishes an authorisation in the`
  line `prescribedform authorisingthe Board or any other income-tax authority acting on its behalf to seek`
  line `relevant information from the said financial institution on behalf of such assessee; and`
  line `( b ) in respect of any other expenditure or allowance (including depreciation) arising from the`
  line `transaction with a person located in a notified jurisdictional area shall be allowed under any other`
  line `provision of this Act, unless the assessee maintains such other documents and furnishes such`
  line `information as may be prescribed, in this behalf.`
  line `( 4 ) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Act, where, in any previous year, the`
  line `assessee has received or credited any sum from any person located in a notified jurisdictional area and the`
  line `assessee does not offer any explanation about the source of the said sum in the hands of such person or in`
  line `the hands of the beneficial owner (if such person is not the beneficial owner of the said sum) or the`
  line `explanation offered by the assessee, in the opinion of the Assessing Officer, is not satisfactory, then, such`
  line `sum shall be deemed to be the income of the assessee for that previous year.`
  line `( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provisions of this Act, where any person located`
  line `in a notified jurisdictional area is entitled to receive any sum or income or amount on which tax is`
  line `deductible under Chapter XVIIB, the tax shall be deducted at the highest of the following rates,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( a ) at the rate or rates in force;`
  line `( b ) at the rate specified in the relevant provisions of this Act;`
  line `( c ) at the rate of thirty per cent.`
  line `( 6 ) In this section, —`
  line `( i ) “person located in a notified jurisdictional area” shall include,—`
  line `( a ) a person who is resident of the notified jurisdictional area;`
  line `( b ) a person, not being an individual, which is established in the notified jurisdictional area;`
  line or
  line `( c ) a permanent establishment of a person not falling in sub-clause ( a ) or sub-clause ( b ), in`
  line `the notified jurisdictional area;`
  line `( ii ) “permanent establishment” shall have the same meaning as defined in clause ( iiia ) of section`
  line 92F;
  line `( iii ) “transaction” shall have the same meaning as defined in clause ( v ) of section 92F.]`
  line `1 [94B. Limitation on interest deduction in certain cases. –– ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in this Act, where an Indian company, or a permanent establishment of a foreign company in India, being`
  line `the borrower, incurs any expenditure by way of interest or of similar nature exceeding one crore rupees`
  line `which is deductible in computing income chargeable under the head “Profits and gains of business or`
  line `profession” in respect of any debt issued by a non resident, being an associated enterprise of such`
  line `borrower, the interest shall not be deductible in computation of income under the said head to the extent`
  line `that it arises from excess interest, as specified in sub-section ( 2 ):`
  line `Provided that where the debt is issued by a lender which is not associated but an associated enterprise`
  line `either provides an implicit or explicit guarantee to such lender or deposits a corresponding and matching`
  line `amount of funds with the lender, such debt shall be deemed to have been issued by an associated`
  line enterprise.
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 43 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_455_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_456:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-456
  sectionNo (456)
  orderNo 456
  title `Page 456`
  content obj_root_law_sections_456_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_456_footnotes
  sourcePage 456
obj_root_law_sections_456_content:
  string
  line 456
  line `( 2 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), the excess interest shall mean an amount of total interest paid`
  line `or payable in excess of thirty per cent. of earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortisation of`
  line `the borrower in the previous year or interest paid or payable to associated enterprises for that previous`
  line `year, whichever is less.`
  line `( 3 ) Nothing contained in sub-section ( 1 ) shall apply to an Indian company or a permanent`
  line `establishment of a foreign company which is engaged in the business of banking or insurance.`
  line `( 4 ) Where for any assessment year, the interest expenditure is not wholly deducted against income`
  line `under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession”, so much of the interest expenditure as has`
  line `not been so deducted, shall be carried forward to the following assessment year or assessment years, and`
  line `it shall be allowed as a deduction against the profits and gains, if any, of any business or profession`
  line `carried on by it and assessable for that assessment year to the extent of maximum allowable interest`
  line `expenditure in accordance with sub-section ( 2 ):`
  line `Provided that no interest expenditure shall be carried forward under this sub-section for more than`
  line `eight assessment years immediately succeeding the assessment year for which the excess interest`
  line `expenditure was first computed.`
  line `( 5 ) For the purposes of this section, the expressions ––`
  line `( i ) “associated enterprise” shall have the meaning assigned to it in sub -section ( 1 ) and sub-section`
  line `( 2 ) of section 92A;`
  line `( ii ) “debt” means any loan, financial instrument, fi nance lease, financial derivative, or any`
  line `arrangement that gives rise to interest, discounts or other finance charges that are deductible in the`
  line `computation of income chargeable under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession”;`
  line `( iii ) “permanent establishment” includes a fixed place of business through which the business of`
  line `the enterprise is wholly or partly carried on.’.]`
  line `1 [CHAPTER XA`
  line `G ENERAL ANTI-AVOIDANCE RULE`
  line `95. Applicability of GeneralAnti-Avoidance Rule. — 2 [ ( 1 )] Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `the Act, an arrangement entered into by an assessee may be declared to be an impermissible avoidance`
  line `arrangement and the consequence in relation to tax arising therefrom may be determined subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter.`
  line `3 [( 2 ) This Chapter shall apply in respect of any assessment year beginning on or after the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2018.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the provisions of this Chapter`
  line `may be applied to any step in, or a part of, the arrangement as they are applicable to the arrangement.`
  line `96. Impermissible avoidance arrangement. — ( 1 ) An impermissible avoidance arrangement means`
  line `an arrangement, the main purpose of which is to obtain a tax benefit, and it —`
  line `( a ) creates rights, or obligations, which are not ordinarily created between persons dealing at`
  line `arm’s length;`
  line `( b ) results, directly or indirectly, in the misuse, or abuse, of the provisions of this Act;`
  line `( c ) lacks commercial substance or is deemed to lack commercial substance under section 97, in`
  line `whole or in part; or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016). Earlier inserted by Act 23 of 2012, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-4-2014)`
  line `2. Section 95 renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 20 of 2015, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 26, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_456_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_457:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-457
  sectionNo (457)
  orderNo 457
  title `Page 457`
  content obj_root_law_sections_457_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_457_footnotes
  sourcePage 457
obj_root_law_sections_457_content:
  string
  line 457
  line `( d ) is entered into, or carried out, by means, or in a manner, which are not ordinarily employed`
  line `for bona fide purposes.`
  line `( 2 ) An arrangement shall be presumed, unless it is proved to the contrary by the assessee, to have`
  line `been entered into, or carried out, for the main purpose of obtaining a tax benefit, if the main purpose of a`
  line `step in, or a part of, the arrangement is to obtain a tax benefit, notwithstanding the fact that the main`
  line `purpose of the whole arrangement is not to obtain a tax benefit.`
  line `97. Arrangement to lack commercial substance. — ( 1 ) An arrangement shall be deemed to lack`
  line `commercial substance, if —`
  line `( a ) the substance or effect of the arrangement as a whole, is inconsistent with, or differs`
  line `significantly from, the form of its individual steps or a part; or`
  line `( b ) it involves or includes —`
  line `( i ) round trip financing;`
  line `( ii ) an accommodating party;`
  line `( iii ) elements that have effect of offsetting or cancelling each other; or`
  line `( iv ) a transaction which is conducted through one or more persons and disguises the value,`
  line `location, source, ownership or control of funds which is the subject matter of such transaction; or`
  line `( c ) it involves the location of an asset or of a transaction or of the place of residence of any party`
  line `which is without any substantial commercial purpose other than obtaining a tax benefit (but for the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter) for a party; or`
  line `( d ) it does not have a significant effect upon the business risks or net cash flows of any party to`
  line `the arrangement apart from any effect attributable to the tax benefit that would be obtained (but for`
  line `the provisions of this Chapter).`
  line `( 2 ) For the purposesof sub-section ( 1 ), round trip financing includes any arrangement in which,`
  line `through a series of transactions —`
  line `( a ) funds are transferred among the parties to the arrangement; and`
  line `( b ) such transactions do not have any substantial commercial purpose other than obtaining the`
  line `tax benefit (but for the provisions of this Chapter),`
  line `without having any regard to —`
  line `( A ) whether or not the funds involved in the round trip financing can be traced to any funds`
  line `transferred to, or received by, any party in connection with the arrangement;`
  line `( B ) the time, or sequence, in which the funds involved in the round trip financing are transferred`
  line `or received; or`
  line `( C ) the means by, or manner in, or mode through, which funds involved in the round trip`
  line `financing are transferred or received.`
  line `( 3 ) For the purposes of this Chapter, a party to an arrangement shall be an accommodating party, if`
  line `the main purpose of the direct or indirect participation of that party in the arrangement, in whole or in`
  line `part, is to obtain, directly or indirectly, a tax benefit (but for the provisions of this Chapter) for the`
  line `assessee whether or not the party is a connected person in relation to any party to the arrangement.`
  line `( 4 ) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that the following may be relevant but shall not be`
  line `sufficient for determining whether an arrangement lacks commercial substance or not, namely: —`
  line `( i ) the period or time for which the arrangement (including operations therein) exists;`
  line `( ii ) the fact of payment of taxes, directly or indirectly, under the arrangement;`
obj_root_law_sections_457_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_458:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-458
  sectionNo (458)
  orderNo 458
  title `Page 458`
  content obj_root_law_sections_458_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_458_footnotes
  sourcePage 458
obj_root_law_sections_458_content:
  string
  line 458
  line `( iii ) the fact that an exit route (including transfer of any activity or business or operations) is`
  line `provided by the arrangement.`
  line `98. Consequences of impermissible avoidance arrangement. — ( 1 ) If an arrangement is declared to`
  line `be an impermissible avoidance arrangement, then, the consequences, in relation to tax, of the`
  line `arrangement, including denial of tax benefit or a benefit under a tax treaty, shall be determined, in such`
  line `manner as is deemed appropriate, in the circumstances of the case, including by way of but not limited to`
  line `the following, namely: —`
  line `( a ) disregarding, combining or recharacterising any step in, or a part or whole of, the`
  line `impermissible avoidance arrangement;`
  line `( b ) treating the impermissible avoidance arrangement as if it had not been entered into or carried`
  line out;
  line `( c ) disregarding any accommodating party or treating any accommodating party and any other`
  line `party as one and the same person;`
  line `( d ) deeming persons who are connected persons in relation to each other to be one and the same`
  line `person for the purposes of determining tax treatment of any amount;`
  line `( e ) reallocating amongst the parties to the arrangement —`
  line `( i ) any accrual, or receipt, of a capital nature or revenue nature; or`
  line `( ii ) any expenditure, deduction, relief or rebate;`
  line `( f ) treating —`
  line `( i ) the place of residence of any party to the arrangement; or`
  line `( ii ) thesitus of an asset or of a transaction,`
  line `at a place other than the place of residence, location of the asset or location of the transaction as`
  line `provided under the arrangement; or`
  line `( g ) considering or looking through any arrangement by disregarding any corporate structure.`
  line `( 2 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), —`
  line `( i ) any equity may be treated as debt or vice versa;`
  line `( ii ) any accrual, or receipt, of a capital nature may be treated as of revenue nature or vice`
  line `versa; or`
  line `( iii ) any expenditure, deduction, relief or rebate may be recharacterised.`
  line `99. Treatment of connected person and accommodating party. — For the purposes of this Chapter,`
  line `in determining whether a tax benefit exists, —`
  line `( i ) the parties who are connected persons in relation to each other may be treated as one and the`
  line `same person;`
  line `( ii ) any accommodating party may be disregarded;`
  line `( iii ) the accommodating party and any other party may be treated as one and the same person;`
  line `( iv ) the arrangement may be considered or looked through by disregarding any corporate`
  line structure.
  line `100. Application of this Chapter. — The provisions of this Chapter shall apply in addition to, or in`
  line `lieu of, any other basis for determination of tax liability.`
  line `101. Framing of guidelines. — The provisions of this Chapter shall be applied in accordance with`
  line `such guidelines and subject to such conditions, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_458_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_459:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-459
  sectionNo (459)
  orderNo 459
  title `Page 459`
  content obj_root_law_sections_459_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_459_footnotes
  sourcePage 459
obj_root_law_sections_459_content:
  string
  line 459
  line `102. Definitions. — In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( 1 ) “arrangement” means any step in, or a part or whole of, any transaction, operation, scheme,`
  line `agreement or understanding, whether enforceable or not, and includes the alienation of any property`
  line `in such transaction, operation, scheme, agreement or understanding;`
  line `( 2 ) “asset” includes property, or right, of any kind;`
  line `( 3 ) “benefit” includes a payment of any kind whether in tangible or intangible form;`
  line `( 4 ) “connected person” means any person who is connected directly or indirectly to another`
  line `person and includes, —`
  line `( a ) any relative of the person, if such person is an individual;`
  line `( b ) any director of the company or any relative of such director, if the person is a company;`
  line `( c ) any partner or member of a firm or association of persons or body of individuals or any`
  line `relative of such partner or member, if the person is a firm or association of persons or body of`
  line individuals;
  line `( d ) any member of the Hindu undivided family or any relative of such member, if the person`
  line `is a Hindu undivided family;`
  line `( e ) any individual who has a substantial interest in the business of the person or any relative`
  line `of such individual;`
  line `( f ) a company, firm or an association of persons or a body of individuals, whether`
  line `incorporated or not, or a Hindu undivided family having a substantial interest in the business of`
  line `the person or any director, partner, or member of the company, firm or association of persons or`
  line `body of individuals or family, or any relative of such director, partner or member;`
  line `( g ) a company, firm or association of persons or body of individuals, whether incorporated or`
  line `not, or a Hindu undivided family, whose director, partner, or member has a substantial interest in`
  line `the business of the person, or family or any relative of such director, partner or member;`
  line `( h ) any other person who carries on a business, if —`
  line `( i ) the person being an individual, or any relative of such person, has a substantial interest`
  line `in the business of that other person; or`
  line `( ii ) the person being a company, firm, association of persons, body of individuals,`
  line `whether incorporated or not, or a Hindu undivided family, or any director, partner or member`
  line `of such company, firm or association of persons or body of individuals or family, or any`
  line `relative of such director, partner or member, has a substantial interest in the business of that`
  line `other person;`
  line `( 5 ) “fund” includes—`
  line `( a ) any cash;`
  line `( b ) cash equivalents; and`
  line `( c ) any right, or obligation, to receive or pay, the cash or cash equivalent;`
  line `( 6 ) “party” includes a person or a permanent establishment which participates or takes part in an`
  line arrangement;
  line `( 7 ) “relative” shall have the meaning assigned to it in the Explanation to clause ( vi ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 56;`
  line `( 8 ) a person shall be deemed to have a substantial interest in the business, if, —`
  line `( a ) in a case where the business is carried on by a company, such person is, at any time`
  line `during the financial year, the beneficial owner of equity shares carrying twenty per cent or more,`
  line `of the voting power; or`
obj_root_law_sections_459_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_460:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-460
  sectionNo (460)
