  content obj_root_law_sections_460_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_460_footnotes
  sourcePage 460
obj_root_law_sections_460_content:
  string
  line 460
  line `( b ) in any other case, such person is, at any time during the financial year, beneficially`
  line `entitled to twenty per cent or more, of the profits of such business;`
  line `( 9 ) “step” includes a measure or an action, particularly one of a series taken in order to deal with`
  line `or achieve a particular thing or object in the arrangement;`
  line `( 10 ) “tax benefit” includes,—`
  line `( a ) a reduction or avoidance or deferral of tax or other amount payable under this Act; or`
  line `( b ) an increase in a refund of tax or other amount under this Act; or`
  line `( c ) a reduction or avoidance or deferral of tax or other amount that would be payable under`
  line `this Act, as a result of a tax treaty; or`
  line `( d ) an increase in a refund of tax or other amount under this Act as a result of a tax treaty; or`
  line `( e ) a reduction in total income; or`
  line `( f ) an increase in loss,`
  line `in the relevant previous year or any other previous year;`
  line `( 11 ) “tax treaty” means an agreement referred to in sub -section ( 1 ) of section 90 or sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) of section 90A.]`
  line `103. Original CHAPTER XI dealing with Additional Income-tax on Undistributed Profits contained`
  line `sections 95 to 109, sub- headings “A.—General”, “ B. — Incomes forming part of total income on which`
  line `no supertax is payable”, “C.— Rebate of super- tax” and “D.— Additional super- tax on undistributed fits”`
  line `and sections 95 to 103 (both inclusive) were omitted by Act 9 of 1965, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `Subsequently Chapter XI containing remaining sections 104 to 109 was omitted by Act 21 of 1987, s. 41`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `104. [ Income-tax on undistributed income of certain companies.] — Omitted by the Finance`
  line `Act, 1987 (11 of 1987), s. 41 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `105. [ Special provisions for certain companies. ] — Omitted by the Finance Act, 1987 (11 of 1987),`
  line `s. 41 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `106. [ Period of limitation for making orders under section 104.] — Omitted by the Finance`
  line `Act, 1987 (11 of 1987), s. 41 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `107. [ Approval of Inspecting Assistant Commissioner for orders under section 104.] — Omitted`
  line `by the Finance Act, 1987 (11 of 1987), s. 41 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `107A. [ Reduction of minimum distribution in certain cases.] — Omitted by the Finance Act, 1987`
  line `(11 of 1987), s. 41 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988). Earlier s. 107A was inserted by the Finance Act, 1964 (20 of 1964),`
  line `s. 26 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1964).`
  line `108. [ Savings for company in which public are substantially interested. ] — Omitted by the Finance`
  line `Act, 1987 (11 of 1987), s. 41 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `109. [ “Distributable income”, “investment company” and “statutory percentage”`
  line `defined. ] — Omitted by the Finance Act, 1987 (11 of 1987), s. 41 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `CHAPTER XII`
  line `D ETERMINATION OF TAX IN CERTAIN SPECIAL CASES`
  line `1 [110. Determination of tax where total income includes income on which no tax is payable. —`
  line `Where there is included in the total income of an assessee any income on which no income-tax is payable`
  line `under the provisions of this Act, the assessee shall be entitled to a deduction, from the amount of income-`
  line `tax with which he is chargeable on his total income, of an amount equal to the income-tax calculated at`
  line `the average rate of income-tax on the amount on which no income-tax is payable.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 32, for section 110 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
obj_root_law_sections_460_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_461:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-461
  sectionNo (461)
