  title `Page 461`
  content obj_root_law_sections_461_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_461_footnotes
  sourcePage 461
obj_root_law_sections_461_content:
  string
  line 461
  line `111. Tax on accumulated balance of recognised provident fund. — ( 1 ) Where the accumulated`
  line `balance due to an employee participating in a recognised provident fund is included in his total income,`
  line `owing to the provisions of rule 8 of Part A of the Fourth Schedule not being applicable, the 1 [Assessing`
  line `Officer] shall calculate the total of the various sums of 2 [tax] in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `sub-rule ( 1 ) of rule 9 thereof.`
  line `( 2 ) Where the accumulated balance due to an employee participating in a recognised provident fund`
  line `which is not included in his total income under the provisions of rule 8 of Part A of the Fourth Schedule`
  line `becomes payable, super-tax shall be calculated in the manner provided in sub-rule ( 2 ) of rule 9 thereof.`
  line `3 [ 111A. Tax on short-term capital gains in certain cases. — ( 1 ) Where the total income of an`
  line `assessee includes any income chargeable under the head “Capital gains”, arising from the transfer of a`
  line `short-term capital asset, being an equity share in a company or a unit of an equity oriented fund 4 [or a unit`
  line `of a business trust] and —`
  line `( a ) the transaction of sale of such equity share or unit is entered into on or after the date on which`
  line `Chapter VII of the Finance (No. 2) Act, 2004 comes into force; and`
  line `( b ) such transaction is chargeable to securities transaction tax under that Chapter,`
  line `the tax payable by the assessee on the total income shall be the aggregate of —`
  line `( i ) the amount of income-tax calculated on such short-term capital gains at the rate of 5 [fifteen`
  line `per cent.]; and`
  line `( ii ) the amount of income-tax payable on the balance amount of the total income as if such`
  line `balance amount were the total income of the assessee:`
  line `Provided that in the case of an individual or a Hindu undivided family, being a resident, where the`
  line `total income as reduced by such short-term capital gains is below the maximum amount which is not`
  line `chargeable to income-tax, then, such short-term capital gains shall be reduced by the amount by which the`
  line `total income as so reduced falls short of the maximum amount which is not chargeable to income-tax and`
  line `the tax on the balance of such short-term capital gains shall be computed at the rate of 6 [fifteen per cent.].`
  line `7 [Provided further that nothing contained in clause ( b ) shall apply to a transaction undertaken on a`
  line `recognised stock exchange located in any International Financial Services Centre and where the`
  line `consideration for such transaction is paid or payable in foreign currency.]`
  line `( 2 ) Where the gross total income of an assessee includes any short-term capital gains referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ), the deduction under Chapter VIA shall be allowed from the gross total income as reduced`
  line `by such capital gains.`
  line `( 3 ) Where the total income of an assessee includes any short-term capital gains referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ), the rebate under section 88 shall be allowed from the income-tax on the total income as`
  line `reduced by such capital gains.`
  line `8 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “equity oriented fund” shall, have the meaning assigned to it in the Explanation to`
  line `clause ( 38 ) of section 10;`
  line `( b ) “International Financial Services Centre” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in`
  line `clause ( q ) of section 2 of the Special Economic Zones Act, 2005 (28 of 2005);`
  line `( c ) “recognised stock exchange” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( ii ) of the`
  line `Explanation 1 to sub-section ( 5 ) of section 43.]]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 33, fo r “income -tax and super- tax” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 21, for “ten per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2009).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 42, for “ten per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2009).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 49 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017). The second proviso omitted by Act 20 of 2015, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `Earlier the same proviso was inserted by Act 25 of 2014, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 49, ibid., for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
