obj_root_law_sections_463_content:
  string
  line 463
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `2 [Provided that where the tax payable in respect of any income arising from the transfer of a`
  line `long-term capital asset, 3 [being listed securities (other than a unit)] 4 [or zero coupon bond], exceeds ten`
  line `per cent of the amount of capital gains before giving effect to the provisions of the second proviso to`
  line `section 48, then, such excess shall be ignored for the purpose of computing the tax payable by the`
  line `assessee:`
  line `5 [Provided further that where the tax payable in respect of any income arising from the transfer of a`
  line `long-term capital asset, being a unit of a Mutual Fund specified under clause ( 23D ) of section 10, during`
  line `the period beginning on the 1st day of April, 2014 and ending on the 10th day of July, 2014, exceeds ten`
  line `per cent. of the amount of capital gains, before giving effect to the provisions of the second proviso to`
  line `section 48, then, such excess shall be ignored for the purpose of computing the tax payable by the`
  line assessee.]
  line `6 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, —`
  line `7 [( a ) the expression “securities” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( h ) of section 2 of`
  line `the Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (32 of 1956);`
  line `( aa ) “listed securities” means the securities which are listed on any recognised stock exchange in`
  line India;
  line `( ab ) “unlisted securities” means securities other than listed securities.`
  line `8 * * * *]]]`
  line `( 2 ) Where the gross total income of an assessee includes any income arising from the transfer of a`
  line `long-term capital asset, the gross total income shall be reduced by the amount of such income and the`
  line `deduction under Chapter VI-A shall be allowed as if the gross total income as so reduced were the gross`
  line `total income of the assessee.`
  line `( 3 ) Where the total income of an assessee includes any income arising from the transfer of a`
  line `long-term capital asset, the total income shall be reduced by the amount of such income and the rebate`
  line `under section 88 shall be allowed from the income-tax on the total income as so reduced.]`
  line `9 [ 112A. Tax on longterm capital gains in certain cases. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in section 112, the tax payable by an assessee on his total income shall be determined in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ), if —`
  line `( i ) the total income includes any income chargeable under the head “Capital gains”;`
  line `( ii ) the capital gains arise from the transfer of a long-term capital asset being an equity share in a`
  line `company or a unit of an equity oriented fund or a unit of a business trust;`
  line `( iii ) securities transaction tax under Chapter VII of the Finance (No.2) Act, 2004 has, —`
  line `( a ) in a case where the long-term capital asset is in the nature of an equity share in a`
  line `company, been paid on acquisition and transfer of such capital asset; or`
  line `1. The Explanation omitted by Act 22 of 1995, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-1996).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 57 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 35, “being listed securities or unit” (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `4. Ins. by 18 of 2005, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 49, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-4-2000). Prior to its Inserted by Act 27 of 1999, s. 57`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 43, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `8. Clause ( b ) omitted by Act 25 of 2014, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019). Earlier omitted by the Finance Act (26 of 1988), s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `Original section was inserted by Act 15 of 1965, s. 11 (w.e.f. 11-9-1965) and later on amended by Act 13 of 1966, s. 22`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1966), 20 of 1967, s. 33 and the Third Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-1968), 42 of 1970, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-1968/1969) and`
  line `21 of 1973, s. 14 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
