obj_root_law_sections_464_content:
  string
  line 464
  line `( b ) in a case where the long-term capital asset is in the nature of a unit of an equity oriented`
  line `fund or a unit of a business trust, been paid on transfer of such capital asset.`
  line `( 2 ) The tax payable by the assessee on the total income referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be the`
  line `aggregate of —`
  line `( i ) the amount of income-tax calculated on such long-term capital gains exceeding one lakh`
  line `rupees at the rate of ten per cent.; and`
  line `( ii ) the amount of income-tax payable on the total income as reduced by the amount of long-term`
  line `capital gains referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) as if the total income so reduced were the total income of`
  line `the assessee:`
  line `Provided that in the case of an individual or a Hindu undivided family, being a resident, where`
  line `the total income as reduced by such long-term capital gains is below the maximum amount which is`
  line `not chargeable to income-tax, then, the long-term capital gains, for the purposes of clause ( i ), shall be`
  line `reduced by the amount by which the total income as so reduced falls short of the maximum amount`
  line `which is not chargeable to income-tax.`
  line `( 3 ) The condition specified in clause ( iii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) shall not apply to a transfer undertaken on`
  line `a recognised stock exchange located in any International Financial Services Centre and where the`
  line `consideration for such transfer is received or receivable in foreign currency.`
  line `( 4 ) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify the nature of`
  line `acquisition in respect of which the provisions of sub-clause ( a ) of clause ( iii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) shall not`
  line apply.
  line `( 5 ) Where the gross total income of an assessee includes any long-term capital gains referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ), the deduction under Chapter VI-A shall be allowed from the gross total income as`
  line `reduced by such capital gains.`
  line `( 6 ) Where the total income of an assessee includes any long-term capital gains referred to in sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ), the rebate under section 87A shall be allowed from the income-tax on the total income as`
  line `reduced by tax payable on such capital gains.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “equity oriented fund” means a fund set up under a scheme of a mutual fund specified under`
  line `clause ( 23D ) of section 10 and, —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the fund invests in the units of another fund which is traded on a`
  line `recognised stock exchange, —`
  line `( A ) a minimum of ninety per cent. of the total proceeds of such fund is invested in the`
  line `units of such other fund; and`
  line `( B ) such other fund also invests a minimum of ninety per cent. of its total proceeds in the`
  line `equity shares of domestic companies listed on a recognised stock exchange; and`
  line `( ii ) in any other case, a minimum of sixty-five per cent. of the total proceeds of such fund is`
  line `invested in the equity shares of domestic companies listed on a recognised stock exchange:`
  line `Provided that the percentage of equity shareholding or unit held in respect of the fund, as the`
  line `case may be, shall be computed with reference to the annual average of the monthly averages of`
  line `the opening and closing figures;`
  line `( b ) “International Financial Services Centre” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( q ) of`
  line `section 2 of the Special Economic Zones Act, 2005;`
  line `( c ) “recognised stock exchange” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( ii ) of`
  line `Explanation 1 to clause ( 5 ) of section 43.`
