obj_root_law_sections_466_content:
  string
  line 466
  line `( C ) the amount of income-tax calculated on the income in respect of units referred to in`
  line `sub-clause ( iii ), if any, included in the total income, at the rate of twenty per cent; and`
  line `( D ) the amount of income-tax with which he or it would have been chargeable had his or its`
  line `total income been reduced by the amount of income referred to in sub-clause ( i ), sub-clause ( ii )`
  line `1 [, sub-clause ( iia )] 2 [, sub-clause ( iiaa )] 3 [, sub-clause ( iiab )] 4 [, sub-clause ( iiac )] and`
  line `sub-clause ( iii );`
  line `( b ) 5 [a non-resident (not being a company) or a foreign company, includes any income by way of`
  line `royalty or fees for technical services other than income referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 44DA]`
  line `received from Government or an Indian concern in pursuance of an agreement made by the foreign`
  line `company with Government or the Indian concern after the 31st day of March, 1976, and where such`
  line `agreement is with an Indian concern, the agreement is approved by the Central Government or where`
  line `it relates to a matter included in the industrial policy, for the time being in force, of the Government`
  line `of India, the agreement is in accordance with that policy, then, subject to the provisions of`
  line `sub-sections ( 1A ) and ( 2 ), the income-tax payable shall be the aggregate of, —`
  line `6 [( A ) the amount of income-tax calculated on the income by way of royalty, if any, included`
  line `in the total income, at the rate of 7 [ten per cent.];`
  line `( B ) the amount of income-tax calculated on the income by way of fees for technical services,`
  line `if any, included in the total income, at the rate of 7 [ten per cent.]; and]`
  line `( C ) the amount of income-tax with which it would have been chargeable had its total income`
  line `been reduced by the amount of income by way of royalty and fees for technical services.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “fees for technical services” shall have the same meaning as in Explanation 2 to clause ( vii )`
  line `of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 9;`
  line `( b ) “foreign currency” shall have the same meaning as in the Explanation below item ( g ) of`
  line `sub-clause ( iv ) of clause ( 15 ) of section 10;`
  line `( c ) “royalty” shall have the same meaning as in Explanation 2 to clause ( vi ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 9;`
  line `( d ) “Unit Trust of India” means the Unit Trust of India established under the Unit Trust of India`
  line `Act, 1963 (52 of 1963).]`
  line `8 [( 1A ) Where the royalty referred to in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) is in consideration for the transfer`
  line `of all or any rights (including the granting of a licence) in respect of copyright in any book to an Indian`
  line `concern 9 [or in respect of any computer software to a person resident in India], the provisions of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) shall apply in relation to such royalty as if the words 10 [ 11 [the agreement is approved by`
  line `the Central Government or where it relates to a matter] included in the industrial policy, for the time`
  line `being in force, of the Government of India, the agreement is in accordance with that policy] occurring in`
  line `the said clause had been omitted:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-6-2011).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 44 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 50, for “a foreign company, includes an y income by way of royalty or fees for technical`
  line `services” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2004).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 27 for sub-clauses ( A ), ( AA ), ( B ) and ( BB ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 28 for “Twenty - five per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2016).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-4-1978).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 54, for “and approved by the Central Government” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1992).`
  line `11. Subs. by 32 of 1994, s. 32, for “approved by the Central Government or where the agreement relates to a matter”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
