obj_root_law_sections_467_content:
  string
  line 467
  line `Provided that such book is on a subject, the books on which are permitted, according to the Import`
  line `Trade Control Policy of the Government of India for the period commencing from the 1st day of April,`
  line `1977, and ending with the 31st day of March, 1978, to be imported into India under an Open General`
  line `Licence:`
  line `1 [Provided further that such computer software is permitted according to the Import Trade Control`
  line `Policy of the Government of India for the time being in force to be imported into India under an Open`
  line `General Licence.]`
  line `2 [ Explanation 1 ]. — In this sub- section, “Open General Licence” means an Open General Licence`
  line `issued by the Central Government in pursuance of the Imports (Control) Order, 1955.]`
  line `3 [ Explanation 2. — In this sub-section, the expression “computer software” shall have the meaning`
  line `assigned to it in clause ( b ) of the Explanation to section 80HHE.]`
  line `( 2 ) Nothing contained in sub-section ( 1 ) shall apply in relation to any income by way of royalty`
  line `received by a foreign company from an Indian concern in pursuance of an agreement made by it with the`
  line `Indian concern after the 31st day of March, 1976, if such agreement is deemed, for the 4 [purposes of the`
  line `first proviso] to clause ( vi ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 9, to have been made before the 1st day of April,`
  line `1976; and the provisions of the annual Finance Act for calculating, charging, deducting or computing`
  line `income-tax shall apply in relation to such income as if such income had been received in pursuance of an`
  line `agreement made before the 1st day of April, 1976.]`
  line `5 [( 3 ) No deduction in respect of any expenditure or allowance shall be allowed to the assessee under`
  line `sections 28 to 44C and section 57 in computing his or its income referred to in sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 4 ) Where in the case of an assessee referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), —`
  line `( a ) the gross total income consists only of the income referred to in clause ( a ) of that sub-section,`
  line `no deduction shall be allowed to him or it under Chapter VI-A;`
  line `( b ) the gross total income includes any income referred to in clause ( a ) of that sub-section, the`
  line `gross total income shall be reduced by the amount of such income and the deduction under Chapter`
  line `VI-A shall be allowed as if the gross total income as so reduced were the gross total income of the`
  line assessee.
  line `( 5 ) It shall not be necessary for an assessee referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) to furnish under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139 a return of his or its income if —`
  line `( a ) his or its total income in respect of which he or it is assessable under this Act during the`
  line `previous year consisted only of income referred to in clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ); and`
  line `( b ) the tax deductible at source under the provisions of Chapter XVII-B has been deducted from`
  line `such income.]`
  line `6 [115AB. Tax on income from units purchased in foreign currency or capital gains arising from`
  line `their transfer. — ( 1 ) Where the total income of an assessee, being an overseas financial organisation`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as Offshore Fund) includes —`
  line `( a ) income received in respect of units purchased in foreign currency; or`
  line `( b ) income by way of long-term capital gains arising from the transfer of units purchased in`
  line `foreign currency,`
  line `the income-tax payable shall be the aggregate of —`
  line `( i ) the amount of income-tax calculated on the income in respect of units referred to in`
  line `clause ( a ), if any, included in the total income, at the rate of ten per cent;`
  line `( ii ) the amount of income-tax calculated on the income by way of long-term capital gains referred`
  line `to in clause ( b ), if any, included in the total income, at the rate of ten per cent; and`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `2. The existing Explanation renumbered as Explanation 1 by s. 40, ibid (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 40, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 40, ibid., for “purposes of the proviso” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1991).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
