obj_root_law_sections_468_content:
  string
  line 468
  line `( iii ) the amount of income-tax with which the Offshore Fund would have been chargeable had its`
  line `total income been reduced by the amount of income referred to in clause ( a ) and clause ( b ).`
  line `( 2 ) Where the gross total income of the Offshore Fund, —`
  line `( a ) consists only of income from units or income by way of long-term capital gains arising from`
  line `the transfer of units, or both, no deduction shall be allowed to the assessee under sections 28 to 44C`
  line `1 *** or clause ( i ) or clause ( iii ) of section 57 or under Chapter VI-A 2 [and nothing contained in the`
  line `provisions of the second proviso to section 48 shall apply to income referred to in clause ( b ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 )];`
  line `( b ) includes any income referred to in clause ( a ), the gross total income shall be reduced by the`
  line `amount of such income and the deduction under Chapter VI-A shall be allowed as if the gross total`
  line `income as so reduced were the gross total income of the assessee.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “overseas financial organisation” means any fund, institution, association or body, whether`
  line `incorporated or not, established under the laws of a country outside India, which has entered into an`
  line `arrangement for investment in India with any public sector bank or public financial institution or a`
  line `mutual fund specified under clause ( 23D ) of section 10 and such arrangement is approved by the`
  line `3 [Securities and Exchange Board of India, established under the Securities and Exchange Board of`
  line `India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992),] for this purpose;`
  line `( b ) “unit” means unit of a mutual fund specified under clause ( 23D ) of section 10 or of the Unit`
  line `Trust of India;`
  line `( c ) “foreign currency” shall have the meaning as in 4 [the Foreign Exchange Management`
  line `Act, 1999 (42 of 1999)];`
  line `( d ) “public sector bank” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( 23D ) of section 10;`
  line `( e ) “public financial institution” shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 4A of the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line `( f ) “Unit Trust of India” me ans the Unit Trust of India established under the Unit Trust of India`
  line `Act, 1963 (52 of 1963)].`
  line `5 [115AC. Tax on income from bonds or Global Depository Receipts purchased in foreign`
  line `currency or capital gains arising from their transfer. — ( 1 ) Where the total income of an assessee,`
  line `being a non- resident, includes —`
  line `( a ) income by way of interest on bonds of an Indian company issued in accordance with such`
  line `scheme as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf,`
  line `or on bonds of a public sector company sold by the Government, and purchased by him in foreign`
  line `currency; or`
  line `( b ) income by way of dividends 6 [, other than dividends referred to in section 115-O,] on Global`
  line `Depository Receipts —`
  line `( i ) issued in accordance with such scheme as the Central Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf, against the initial issue of shares of an Indian company`
  line `and purchased by him in foreign currency through an approved intermediary; or`
  line `( ii ) issued against the shares of a public sector company sold by the Government and`
  line `purchased by him in foreign currency through an approved intermediary; or`
  line `1. The words, brackets and figures “or sub -section ( 2 ) of section 48” omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 55 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1993).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 55, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 51, for “Central Government” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2001).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 4, for “the Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 52, for section 115AC (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 50, for “dividends” (w.e.f. 1 -4- 2004). Earlier the words, figures and letter “other than`
  line `dividends referred to in section 115- O” omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1 -4-2003).`
