obj_root_law_sections_469_content:
  string
  line 469
  line `( iii ) 1 [issued or re-issued] in accordance with such scheme as the Central Government may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf, against the existing shares of an`
  line `Indian company purchased by him in foreign currency through an approved intermediary; or`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `( c ) income by way of long-term capital gains arising from the transfer of bonds referred to in`
  line `clause ( a ) or, as the case may be, Global Depository Receipts referred to in clause ( b ),`
  line `the income-tax payable shall be the aggregate of —`
  line `( i ) the amount of income-tax calculated on the income by way of interest or dividends 3 [, other`
  line `than dividends referred to in section 115-O ], as the case may be, in respect of bonds referred to in`
  line `clause ( a ) or Global Depository Receipts referred to in clause ( b ), if any, included in the total income,`
  line `at the rate of ten per cent;`
  line `( ii ) the amount of income-tax calculated on the income by way of long-term capital gains`
  line `referred to in clause ( c ), if any, at the rate of ten per cent; and`
  line `( iii ) the amount of income-tax with which the non-resident would have been chargeable had his`
  line `total income been reduced by the amount of income referred to in clauses ( a ), ( b ) and ( c ).`
  line `( 2 ) Where the gross total income of the non-resident —`
  line `( a ) consists only of income by way of interest or dividends 2 [, other than dividends referred to`
  line `in section 115-O ] in respect of bonds referred to in clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ) or, as the case may`
  line `be, Global Depository Receipts referred to in clause ( b ) of that sub-section, no deduction shall be`
  line `allowed to him under sections 28 to 44C or clause ( i ) or clause ( iii ) of section 57 or under Chapter VI-`
  line A;
  line `( b ) includes any income referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ) of sub-section (1), the`
  line `gross total income shall be reduced by the amount of such income and the deduction under Chapter`
  line `VI-A shall be allowed as if the gross total income as so reduced, were the gross total income of the`
  line assessee.
  line `( 3 ) Nothing contained in the first and second provisos to section 48 shall apply for the computation of`
  line `long-term capital gains arising out of the transfer of long-term capital asset, being bonds or Global`
  line `Depository Receipts referred to in clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 4 ) It shall not be necessary for a non-resident to furnish under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139 a return`
  line `of his income if —`
  line `( a ) his total income in respect of which he is assessable under this Act during the previous year`
  line `consisted only of income referred to in clauses ( a ) and ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ); and`
  line `( b ) the tax deductible at source under the provisions of Chapter XVII-B has been deducted from`
  line `such income.`
  line `( 5 ) Where the assessee acquired Global Depository Receipts or bonds in an amalgamated or resulting`
  line `company by virtue of his holding Global Depository Receipts or bonds in the amalgamating or demerged`
  line `company, as the case may be, in accordance with the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ), the provisions of that`
  line `sub-section shall apply to such Global Depository Receipts or bonds.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “approved intermediary” means an intermediary who is approved in accordance with such`
  line `scheme as may be notified by the Central Government in the Official Gazette;`
  line `( b ) “Global Depository Receipts” shall have the same meaning as in clause ( a ) of`
  line `the Explanation to section 115ACA.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 46, for “re - issued” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2002).`
  line `2. Sub-clause ( iv ) omitted by s. 46, ibid (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 51, for “dividends” (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_469_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_470:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-470
  sectionNo (470)
  orderNo 470
  title `Page 470`
  content obj_root_law_sections_470_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_470_footnotes
  sourcePage 470
obj_root_law_sections_470_content:
  string
  line 470
  line `1 [115ACA. Tax on income from Global Depository Receipts purchased in foreign currency or`
  line `capital gains arising from their transfer. — 2 [( 1 ) Where the total income of an assessee, being an`
  line `individual, who is a resident and an employee of an Indian company engaged in specified knowledge`
  line `based industry or service, or an employee of its subsidiary engaged in specified knowledge based industry`
  line `or service (hereafter in this section referred to as the resident employee), includes —`
  line `( a ) 3 [income by way of dividends, other than dividends referred to in section 115-O], on Global`
  line `Depository Receipts of an Indian company engaged in specified knowledge based industry or service,`
  line `issued in accordance with such Employees’ Stock Option Scheme as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf and purchased by him in foreign currency;`
  line or
  line `( b ) income by way of long-term capital gains arising from the transfer of Global Depository`
  line `Receipts referred to in clause ( a ),`
  line `the income-tax payable shall be the aggregate of —`
  line `( i ) the amount of income-tax calculated on the 3 [income by way of dividends, other than`
  line `dividends referred to in section 115-O], in respect of Global Depository Receipts referred to in`
  line `clause ( a ), if any, included in the total income, at the rate of ten per cent;`
  line `( ii ) the amount of income-tax calculated on the income by way of long-term capital gains`
  line `referred to in clause ( b ), if any, at the rate of ten per cent; and`
  line `( iii ) the amount of income-tax with which the resident employee would have been chargeable had`
  line `his total income been reduced by the amount of income referred to in clauses ( a ) and ( b ).`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, —`
  line `( a ) “specified knowledge based industry or service” means—`
  line `( i ) information technology software;`
  line `( ii ) information technology service;`
  line `( iii ) entertainment service;`
  line `( iv ) pharmaceutical industry;`
  line `( v ) bio-technology industry; and`
  line `( vi ) any other industry or service, as may be specified by the Central Government, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette;`
  line `( b ) “subsidiary” shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 4 of the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956) and includes subsidiary incorporated outside India.]`
  line `( 2 ) Where the gross total income of the resident employee —`
  line `( a ) consists only of 3 [income by way of dividends, other than dividends referred to in`
  line `section 115-O], in respect of Global Depository Receipts referred to in clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ),`
  line `no deduction shall be allowed to him under any other provision of this Act;`
  line `( b ) includes any income referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ), the gross total`
  line `income shall be reduced by the amount of such income and the deduction under any provision of this`
  line `Act shall be allowed as if the gross total income as so reduced were the gross total income of the`
  line assessee.
  line `( 3 ) Nothing contained in the first and second provisos to section 48 shall apply for the computation of`
  line `long-term capital gains arising out of the transfer of long-term capital asset, being Global Depository`
  line `Receipts referred to in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 59 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 53, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 52, for “income by way of dividends” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_470_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_471:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-471
  sectionNo (471)
  orderNo 471
  title `Page 471`
  content obj_root_law_sections_471_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_471_footnotes
  sourcePage 471
obj_root_law_sections_471_content:
  string
  line 471
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “Global Depository Receipts” means any instrument in the form of a depository receipt or`
  line `certificate (by whatever name called) created by the Overseas Depository Bank outside India`
  line `and 1 [issued to investors against the issue of, —`
  line `( i ) ordinary shares of issuing company, being a company listed on a recognised stock`
  line `exchange in India; or`
  line `( ii ) foreign currency convertible bonds of issuing company];`
  line `( b ) “information technology service” means any service which results from the use of any`
  line `information technology software over a system of information technology products for realising value`
  line addition;
  line `( c ) “information technology software” means any representation of instructions, data, sound or`
  line `image, including source code and object code, recorded in a machine readable form and capable of`
  line `being manipulated or providing inter-activity to a user, by means of an automatic data processing`
  line `machine falling under heading information technology products but does not include non-information`
  line `technology products;`
  line `( d ) “Overseas Depository Bank” means a bank authorised by the issuing company to issue Global`
  line `Depository Receipts against issue of Foreign Currency Convertible Bonds or ordinary shares of the`
  line `issuing company.]`
  line `2 [115AD. Tax on income of Foreign Institutional Investors from securities or capital gains`
  line `arising from their transfer. — ( 1 ) Where the total income of a Foreign Institutional Investor includes —`
  line `3 [( a ) 4 [income other than income by way of dividends referred to in section 115-O] received in`
  line `respect of securities (other than units referred to in section 115AB); or]`
  line `( b ) income by way of short-term or long-term capital gains arising from the transfer of such`
  line securities,
  line `the income-tax payable shall be the aggregate of —`
  line `( i ) the amount of income-tax calculated on the income in respect of securities referred to in`
  line `clause ( a ), if any, included in the total income, at the rate of twenty per cent:`
  line `5 [Provided that the amount of income-tax calculated on the income by way of interest referred to`
  line `in section 194LD shall be at the rate of five per cent.;]`
  line `( ii ) the amount of income-tax calculated on the income by way of short-term capital gains`
  line `referred to in clause ( b ), if any, included in the total income, at the rate of thirty per cent:`
  line `6 [Provided that the amount of income-tax calculated on the income by way of short-term capital`
  line `gains referred to in section 111A shall be at the rate of 7 [fifteen per cent.];]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 29, for “issued to non -resident inventors against the issue of ordinary shares or foreign`
  line `currency convertible bonds of issuing company” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2016).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 38 of 1993, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 38, for clasue ( a ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 53, for “income” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2004).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 22, for “ten per cent.” (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_471_footnotes:
