  line
obj_root_law_sections_472:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-472
  sectionNo (472)
  orderNo 472
  title `Page 472`
  content obj_root_law_sections_472_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_472_footnotes
  sourcePage 472
obj_root_law_sections_472_content:
  string
  line 472
  line `( iii ) the amount of income-tax calculated on the income by way of long-term capital gains`
  line `referred to in clause ( b ), if any, included in the total income, at the rate of ten per cent.; 1 ***`
  line `2 [Provided that in case of income arising from the transfer of a long-term capital asset referred to`
  line `in section 112A, income-tax at the rate of ten per cent. shall be calculated on such income exceeding`
  line `one lakh rupees; and]`
  line `( iv ) the amount of income-tax with which the Foreign Institutional Investor would have been`
  line `chargeable had its total income been reduced by the amount of income referred to in clause ( a ) and`
  line `clause ( b ).`
  line `( 2 ) Where the gross total income of the Foreign Institutional Investor —`
  line `( a ) consists only of income in respect of securities referred to in clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ), no`
  line `deduction shall be allowed to it under sections 28 to 44C or clause ( i ) or clause ( iii ) of section 57 or`
  line `under Chapter VIA;`
  line `( b ) includes any income referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ), the gross total`
  line `income shall be reduced by the amount of such income and the deduction under Chapter VIA shall be`
  line `allowed as if the gross total income as so reduced, were the gross total income of the Foreign`
  line `Institutional Investor.`
  line `( 3 ) Nothing contained in the first and second provisos to section 48 shall apply for the computation of`
  line `capital gains arising out of the transfer of securities referred to in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) the expression “Foreign Institutional Investor” means such investor as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf;`
  line `( b ) the expression “securities” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( h ) of section 2 of`
  line `the Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956).]`
  line `115B. Tax on profits and gains of life insurance business. — 3 [( 1 )] Where the total income of an`
  line `assessee includes any profits and gains from life insurance business, the income-tax payable shall be the`
  line `aggregate of —`
  line `( i ) the amount of income-tax calculated on the amount of profits and gains of the life insurance`
  line `business included in the total income, at the rate of twelve and one-half per cent; and`
  line `( ii ) the amount of income-tax with which the assessee would have been chargeable had the total`
  line `income of the assessee been reduced by the amount of profits and gains of the life insurance business.`
  line `4 [( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ) or in any other law for the time being in`
  line `force or any instrument having the force of law, the assessee shall, in addition to the payment of income-`
  line `tax computed under sub-section ( 1 ), deposit, during 5 [the previous years relevant to the assessment years`
  line `commencing on the 1st day of April, 1989 and the 1st day of April, 1990], an amount equal to thirty-three`
  line `and one-third per cent of the amount of income-tax computed under clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ), in such`
  line `social security fund (hereafter in this sub-section referred to as the security fund), as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf:`
  line `1. The word “and” omitted by Act 13 of 2018, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1 -4-2019).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 34, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
  line `3. Section 115B renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) by Act 26 of 1988, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 31, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 13 of 1989, s. 18, for “the previous year relevant to the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April,`
  line `1989” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1990).`
