  content obj_root_law_sections_473_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_473_footnotes
  sourcePage 473
obj_root_law_sections_473_content:
  string
  line 473
  line `Provided that where the assessee makes during the said 1 [previous years] any deposit of an amount of`
  line `not less than two and one-half per cent of the profits and gains of the life insurance business in the`
  line `security fund, the amount of income-tax payable by the assessee under the said clause ( i ) shall be reduced`
  line `by an amount equal to two and one-half per cent of such profits and gains and, accordingly, the deposit of`
  line `thirty-three and one-third per cent required to be made under this sub-section shall be calculated on the`
  line `income-tax as so reduced].]`
  line `2 [115BA. Tax on income of certain domestic companies. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in this Act but subject to the 3 [other provisions of this Chapter], the income-tax payable in respect of the`
  line `total income of a person, being a domestic company, for any previous year relevant to the assessment year`
  line `beginning on or after the 1st day of April, 2017, shall, at the option of such person, be computed at the`
  line `rate of twenty-five per cent, if the conditions contained in sub-section ( 2 ) are satisfied.`
  line `( 2 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), the following conditions shall apply, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the company has been set-up and registered on or after the 1st day of March, 2016;`
  line `( b ) the company is not engaged in any business other than the business of manufacture or`
  line `production of any article or thing and research in relation to, or distribution of, such article or thing`
  line `manufactured or produced by it; and`
  line `( c ) the total income of the company has been computed, —`
  line `( i ) without any deduction under the provisions of section 10AA or clause ( iia )`
  line `of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 32 or section 32AC or section 32AD or section 33AB or section`
  line `33ABA or sub-clause ( ii ) or sub-clause ( iia ) or sub-clause ( iii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section`
  line `( 2AA ) or sub-section ( 2AB ) of section 35 or section 35AC or section 35AD or section`
  line `35CCC or section 35CCD or under any provisions of Chapter VIA under the heading “C.—`
  line `Deductions in respect of certain incomes” other than the provisions of section 80JJAA;`
  line `( ii ) without set off of any loss carried forward from any earlier assessment year if such loss is`
  line `attributable to any of the deductions referred to in sub-clause ( i ); and`
  line `( iii ) depreciation under section 32, other than clause ( iia ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of the said`
  line `section, is determined in the manner as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 3 ) The loss referred to in sub-clause ( ii ) of clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 2 ) shall be deemed to have been`
  line `already given full effect to and no further deduction for such loss shall be allowed for any subsequent`
  line year.
  line `( 4 ) Nothing contained in this section shall apply unless the option is exercised by the person in the`
  line `prescribed manner on or before the due date specified under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139 for furnishing`
  line `the first of the returns of income which the person is required to furnish under the provisions of this Act:`
  line `Provided that once the option has been exercised for any previous year, it cannot be subsequently`
  line `withdrawn for the same or any other previous year.]`
  line `4 [115BB. Tax on winnings from lotteries, crossword puzzles, races including horse races,`
  line `card games and other games of any sort or gambling or betting of any form or nature`
  line `whatsoever. — Where the total income of an assessee includes any income by way of winnings from any`
  line `lottery or crossword puzzle or race including horse race (not being income from the activity of owning`
  line `and maintaining race horses) or card game and other game of any sort or from gambling or betting of any`
  line `form or nature whatsoever, the income-tax payable shall be the aggregate of —`
  line `( i ) the amount of income-tax calculated on income by way of winnings from such lottery or`
  line `crossword puzzle or race including horse race or card game and other game of any sort or from`
  line `gambling or betting of any form or nature whatsoever, at the rate of 5 [thirty per cent.]; and`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 1989, s. 18, for “previous year” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1990).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 51 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 35, for “provisions of section 111A and section 112” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 3 of 1986, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 54, for “forty per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2002).`
