obj_root_law_sections_474_content:
  string
  line 474
  line `( ii ) the amount of income-tax with which the assessee would have been chargeable had his total`
  line `income been reduced by the amount of income referred to in clause ( i ).`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, “horse race” shall have the same meaning as`
  line `in section 74A.]`
  line `1 [115BBA. Tax on non-resident sportsmen or sports associations. — ( 1 ) Where the total income of`
  line `an assessee, —`
  line `( a ) being a sportsman (including an athlete), who is not a citizen of India and is a non-resident,`
  line `includes any income received or receivable by way of —`
  line `( i ) participation in India in any game (other than a game the winnings wherefrom are taxable`
  line `under section 115BB) or sport; or`
  line `( ii ) advertisement; or`
  line `( iii ) contribution of articles relating to any game or sport in India in newspapers, magazines`
  line `or journals; or`
  line `( b ) being a non-resident sports association or institution, includes any amount guaranteed to be`
  line `paid or payable to such association or institution in relation to any game (other than a game the`
  line `winnings wherefrom are taxable under section 115BB) or sport played in India 2 [; or]`
  line `2 [( c ) being an entertainer, who is not a citizen of India and is a non-resident, includes any income`
  line `received or receivable from his performance in India,]`
  line `the income-tax payable by the assessee shall be the aggregate of —`
  line `( i ) the amount of income-tax calculated on income referred to in 3 [clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or`
  line `clause ( c )] at the rate of 4 [twenty per cent.]; and`
  line `( ii ) the amount of income-tax with which the assessee would have been chargeable had the total`
  line `income of the assessee been reduced by the amount of income referred to in 3 [clause ( a ) or clause ( b )`
  line `or clause ( c )]:`
  line `Provided that no deduction in respect of any expenditure or allowance shall be allowed under any`
  line `provision of this Act in computing the income referred to in 3 [clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or clause ( c )].`
  line `( 2 ) It shall not be necessary for the assessee to furnish under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139 a return of`
  line `his income if —`
  line `( a ) his total income in respect of which he is assessable under this Act during the previous year`
  line `consisted only of income referred to in 3 [clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or clause ( c )] of sub-section ( 1 ); and`
  line `( b ) the tax deductible at source under the provisions of Chapter XVIIB has been deducted from`
  line `such income.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 36 of 1989, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 45, ibid., for “clause ( a ) or clause ( b )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 45, ibid., for “ten per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
