  content obj_root_law_sections_475_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_475_footnotes
  sourcePage 475
obj_root_law_sections_475_content:
  string
  line 475
  line `1 [ 115BBB. Tax on income from units of an open-ended equity oriented fund of the Unit Trust of`
  line `India or of Mutual Funds. — ( 1 ) Where the total income of an assessee includes any income from units`
  line `of an open-ended equity oriented fund of the Unit Trust of India or of a Mutual Fund, the income-tax`
  line `payable shall be the aggregate of —`
  line `( a ) the amount of income-tax calculated on income from units of an open-ended equity oriented`
  line `fund of the Unit Trust of India or of a Mutual Fund, at the rate of ten per cent; and`
  line `( b ) the amount of income-tax with which the assessee would have been chargeable had his total`
  line `income been reduced by the amount of income referred to in clause ( a ).`
  line `( 2 ) Nothing contained in sub-section ( 1 ) shall apply in relation to any income from units of an open-`
  line `ended equity oriented fund of the Unit Trust of India or of the Mutual Fund arising after the 31st day of`
  line `March, 2003.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, the expressions “Mutual Fund”, “open -ended equity`
  line `oriented fund” and “Unit Trust of India” shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in`
  line `the Explanation to section 115T.]`
  line `2 [ 115BBC. Anonymous donations to be taxed in certain cases. — ( 1 ) Where the total income of an`
  line `assessee, being a person in receipt of income on behalf of any university or other educational institution`
  line `referred to in sub-clause ( iiiad ) or sub-clause ( vi ) or any hospital or other institution referred to in sub-`
  line `clause ( iiiae ) or sub-clause ( via ) or any fund or institution referred to in sub-clause ( iv ) or any trust or`
  line `institution referred to in sub-clause ( v ) of clause ( 23C ) of section 10 or any trust or institution referred to`
  line `in section 11, includes any income by way of any anonymous donation, the income-tax payable shall be`
  line `the aggregate of —`
  line `3 [( i ) the amount of income-tax calculated at the rate of thirty per cent. on the aggregate of`
  line `anonymous donations received in excess of the higher of the following, namely: —`
  line `( A ) five per cent of the total donations received by the assessee; or`
  line `( B ) one lakh rupees, and]`
  line `4 [( ii ) the amount of income-tax with which the assessee would have been chargeable had his total`
  line `income been reduced by the aggregate of anonymous donations received in excess of the amount`
  line `referred to in sub-clause ( A ) or sub-clause ( B ) of clause ( i ), as the case may be.]`
  line `( 2 ) The provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) shall not apply to any anonymous donation received by —`
  line `( a ) any trust or institution created or established wholly for religious purposes;`
  line `( b ) any trust or institution created or established wholly for religious and charitable purposes`
  line `other than any anonymous donation made with a specific direction that such donation is for any`
  line `university or other educational institution or any hospital or other medical institution run by such trust`
  line `or institution.`
  line `( 3 ) For the purposes of this section, “anonymous donation” means any voluntary contribution referred`
  line `to in sub-clause ( iia ) of clause ( 24 ) of section 2, where a person receiving such contribution does not`
  line `maintain a record of the identity indicating the name and address of the person making such contribution`
  line `and such other particulars as may be prescribed.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 49 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 43, for clause ( i ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 37, for clause ( ii ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
