obj_root_law_sections_476_content:
  string
  line 476
  line `1 [ 115BBD. Tax on certain dividends received from foreign companies. — ( 1 ) Where the total`
  line `income of an assessee, being an Indian company, 2 *** includes any income by way of dividends declared,`
  line `distributed or paid by a specified foreign company, the income-tax payable shall be the aggregate of —`
  line `( a ) the amount of income-tax calculated on the income by way of such dividends, at the rate of`
  line `fifteen per cent; and`
  line `( b ) the amount of income-tax with which the assessee would have been chargeable had its total`
  line `income been reduced by the aforesaid income by way of dividends.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, no deduction in respect of any expenditure or`
  line `allowance shall be allowed to the assessee under any provision of this Act in computing its income by`
  line `way of dividends referred to in sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 3 ) In this section, —`
  line `( i ) “dividends” shall have the same meaning as is given to “dividend” in clause ( 22 ) of`
  line `section 2 but shall not include sub-clause ( e ) thereof;`
  line `( ii ) “specified foreign company” means a foreign company in which the Indian company holds`
  line `twenty-six per cent or more in nominal value of the equity share capital of the company.]`
  line `3 [ 115BBDA. Tax on certain dividends received from domestic companies. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act, where the total income of 4 [a specified assessee,] resident in India,`
  line `includes any income in aggregate exceeding ten lakh rupees, by way of dividends declared, distributed or`
  line `paid by a domestic company or companies, the income-tax payable shall be the aggregate of —`
  line `( a ) the amount of income-tax calculated on the income by way of such dividends in aggregate`
  line `exceeding ten lakh rupees, at the rate of ten per cent; and`
  line `( b ) the amount of income-tax with which the assessee would have been chargeable had the total`
  line `income of the assessee been reduced by the amount of income by way of dividends.`
  line `( 2 ) No deduction in respect of any expenditure or allowance or set off of loss shall be allowed to the`
  line `assessee under any provision of this Act in computing the income by way of dividends referred to in`
  line `clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1).`
  line `( 3 ) In this section, “dividends” shall have the same meaning as is given to “dividend” in clause ( 22 )`
  line `of section 2 but shall not include sub-clause ( e ) thereof.]`
  line `5 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “dividend” shall have the meaning ass igned to it in clause ( 22 ) of section 2 but shall not`
  line `include sub-clause ( e ) thereof;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2012).`
  line `2. The words “for the previous year relevant to the assessment year beginning on the 1st day of April, 2012 or beginning on`
  line `the 1st day of April, 2013 or beginning on the 1st day of April, 2014” omitted by Act 25 of 2014, s. 38 (w. e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 52 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 44, for “an assessee, being an individual, a Hindu Undivided Family or a`
  line `firm” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2018).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 44, ibid., for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_476_footnotes:
