  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_477_footnotes
  sourcePage 477
obj_root_law_sections_477_content:
  string
  line 477
  line `( b ) “ specified assessee ” means a person other than, —`
  line `( i ) a domestic company; or`
  line `( ii ) a fund or institution or trust or any university or other educational institution or any`
  line `hospital or other medical institution referred to in sub-clause ( iv ) or sub-clause ( v ) or`
  line `sub-clause ( vi ) or sub-clause ( via ) of clause ( 23C ) of section 10; or`
  line `( iii ) a trust or institution registered under section 12A or section 12AA.]`
  line `1 [ 115BBE. Tax on income referred to in section 68 or section 69 or section 69A or section 69B or`
  line `section 69C or section 69D. — 2 [( 1 ) Where the total income of an assessee, —`
  line `( a ) includes any income referred to in section 68, section 69, section 69A, section 69B,`
  line `section 69C or section 69D and reflected in the return of income furnished under section 139; or`
  line `( b ) determined by the Assessing Officer includes any income referred to in section 68,`
  line `section 69, section 69A, section 69B, section 69C or section 69D, if such income is not covered under`
  line `clause ( a ),`
  line `the income-tax payable shall be the aggregate of —`
  line `( i ) the amount of income-tax calculated on the income referred to in clause ( a ) and clause ( b ), at`
  line `the rate of sixty per cent; and`
  line `( ii ) the amount of income-tax with which the assessee would have been chargeable had his total`
  line `income been reduced by the amount of income referred to in clause ( i ).]`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, no deduction in respect of any expenditure or`
  line `allowance 3 [or set off of any loss] shall be allowed to the assessee under any provision of this Act in`
  line `computing his income referred to in clause ( a ) 4 [and clause ( b )] of sub-section ( 1 ).]`
  line `5 [ 115BBF. Tax on income from patent. — ( 1 ) Where the total income of an eligible assessee`
  line `includes any income by way of royalty in respect of a patent developed and registered in India, the`
  line `incometax payable shall be the aggregate of —`
  line `( a ) the amount of income-tax calculated on the income by way of royalty in respect of the patent`
  line `at the rate of ten per cent.; and`
  line `( b ) the amount of income-tax with which the assessee would have been chargeable had his total`
  line `income been reduced by the income referred to in clause ( a ).`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, no deduction in respect of any expenditure or`
  line `allowance shall be allowed to the eligible assessee under any provision of this Act in computing his`
  line `income referred to in clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 3 ) The eligible assessee may exercise the option for taxation of income by way of royalty in respect`
  line `of a patent developed and registered in India in accordance with the provisions of this section, in the`
  line `prescribed manner, on or before the due date specified under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139 for furnishing`
  line `the return of income for the relevant previous year.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 48 of 2016, s. 2, for section 115BBE (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 53 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 36 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 54 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
