  string
  line 478
  line `( 4 ) Where an eligible assessee opts for taxation of income by way of royalty in respect of a patent`
  line `developed and registered in India for any previous year in accordance with the provisions of this section`
  line `and the assessee offers the income for taxation for any of the five assessment years relevant to the`
  line `previous year succeeding the previous year not in accordance with the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ), then,`
  line `the assessee shall not be eligible to claim the benefit of the provisions of this section for five assessment`
  line `years subsequent to the assessment year relevant to the previous year in which such income has not been`
  line `offered to tax in accordance with the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “developed” means at least seventy -five per cent. of the expenditure incurred in India by the`
  line `eligible assessee for any invention in respect of which a patent is granted under the Patents Act, 1970`
  line `(herein referred to as the Patents Act);`
  line `( b ) “eligibleassessee” means a person resident in India and who is a patentee;`
  line `( c ) “invention” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( j ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 2`
  line `of the Patents Act;`
  line `( d ) “lump sum” i ncludes an advance payment on account of such royalties which is not`
  line returnable;
  line `( e ) “patent” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( m ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 2 of`
  line `the Patents Act;`
  line `( f) “patentee” means the person, being the true and first inventor of the invention, whose name is`
  line `entered on the patent register as the patentee, in accordance with the Patents Act, and includes every`
  line `such person, being the true and first inventor of the invention, where more than one person is`
  line `registered as patentee under that Act in respect of that patent;`
  line `( g ) “patented article” and “patented process” shall have the meanings respectively assigned to`
  line `them in clause ( o ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 2 of the Patents Act;`
  line `( h ) “royalty”, in respect of a patent, mea ns consideration (including any lump sum consideration`
  line `but excluding any consideration which would be the income of the recipient chargeable under the`
  line `head “Capital gains” or consideration for sale of product manufactured with the use of patented`
  line `process or the patented article for commercial use) for the —`
  line `( i ) transfer of all or any rights (including the granting of a licence) in respect of a patent; or`
  line `( ii ) imparting of any information concerning the working of, or the use of, a patent; or`
  line `( iii ) use of any patent; or`
  line `( iv ) rendering of any services in connection with the activities referred to in sub-clauses ( i )`
  line `to ( iii );`
  line `( i ) “true and first inventor” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( y ) of sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 2 of the Patents Act.]`
