obj_root_law_sections_479_content:
  string
  line 479
  line `1 [115BBG. Tax on income from transfer of carbon credits. — ( 1 ) Where the total income of an`
  line `assessee includes any income by way of transfer of carbon credits, the income-tax payable shall be the`
  line `aggregate of —`
  line `( a ) the amount of income-tax calculated on the income by way of transfer of carbon credits, at`
  line `the rate of ten per cent; and`
  line `( b ) the amount of income-tax with which the assessee would have been chargeable had his total`
  line `income been reduced by the amount of income referred to in clause ( a ).`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, no deduction in respect of any expenditure or`
  line `allowance shall be allowed to the assessee under any provision of this Act in computing his income`
  line `referred to in clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, “carbon credit” in respect of one unit shall mean`
  line `reduction of one tonne of carbon dioxide emissions or emissions of its equivalent gases which is validated`
  line `by the United Nations Framework on Climate Change and which can be traded in market at its prevailing`
  line `market price.]`
  line `2 [CHAPTER XII-A`
  line `S PECIAL PROVISIONS RELATING TO CERTAIN INCOMES OF NON-RESIDENTS`
  line `115C. Definitions. — In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “convertible foreign exchange” means foreign exchange which is for the time being treated by`
  line `the Reserve Bank of India as convertible foreign exchange for the purposes of 3 [the Foreign Exchange`
  line `Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999),] and any rules made thereunder;`
  line `( b ) “foreign exchange asset” means any specified asset which the assessee has acquired or`
  line `purchased with, or subscribed to in, convertible foreign exchange;`
  line `( c ) “investment income” means any 4 [income derived other than dividends referred to in section`
  line `115-O] from a foreign exchange asset;`
  line `( d ) “long - term capital gains” means income chargeable under the head “Capital gains” relating to`
  line `a capital asset, being a foreign exchange asset which is not a short-term capital asset;`
  line `( e ) “non - resident Indian” mea ns an individual, being a citizen of India or a person of Indian`
  line `origin who is not a “resident”.`
  line `Explanation. — A person shall be deemed to be of Indian origin if he, or either of his parents or`
  line `any of his grand-parents, was born in undivided India;`
  line `( f ) “specified asset” means any of the following assets, namely:—`
  line `( i ) shares in an Indian company;`
  line `( ii ) debentures issued by an Indian company which is not a private company as defined in the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line `( iii ) deposits with an Indian company which is not a private company as defined in the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 11 of 1983, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-6-1983).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 4, for “The Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 54, for “income - derive” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2004).`
