obj_root_law_sections_480_content:
  string
  line 480
  line `( iv ) any security of the Central Government as defined in clause ( 2 ) of section 2 of the Public`
  line `Debt Act, 1944 (18 of 1944);`
  line `( v ) such other assets as the Central Government may specify in this behalf by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette.`
  line `115D. S pecial provision for computation of total income of non-residents. — ( 1 ) No deduction in`
  line `respect of any expenditure or allowance shall be allowed under any provision of this Act in computing the`
  line `investment income of a non-resident Indian.`
  line `( 2 ) Where in the case of an assessee, being a non-resident Indian, —`
  line `( a ) the gross total income consists only of investment income or income by way of long-term`
  line `capital gains or both, no deduction shall be allowed to the assessee 1 [under Chapter VI-A and nothing`
  line `contained in the provisions of the second proviso to section 48 shall apply to income chargeable`
  line `under the head “Capital gains”];`
  line `( b ) the gross total income includes any income referred to in clause ( a ), the gross total income`
  line `shall be reduced by the amount of such income and the deductions under Chapter VIA shall be`
  line `allowed as if the gross total income as so reduced were the gross total income of the assessee.`
  line `2 [ 115E. Tax on investment income and long-term capital gains. — Where the total income of an`
  line `assessee, being a non-resident Indian, includes —`
  line `( a ) any income from investment or income from long-term capital gains of an asset other than a`
  line `specified asset;`
  line `( b ) income by way of long-term capital gains,`
  line `the tax payable by him shall be the aggregate of —`
  line `( i ) the amount of income-tax calculated on the income in respect of investment income referred`
  line `to in clause ( a ), if any, included in the total income, at the rate of twenty per cent;`
  line `( ii ) the amount of income-tax calculated on the income by way of long-term capital gains`
  line `referred to in clause ( b ), if any, included in the total income, at the rate of ten per cent; and`
  line `( iii ) the amount of income-tax with which he would have been chargeable had his total income`
  line `been reduced by the amount of income referred to in clauses ( a ) and ( b ).]`
  line `115F. Capital gains on transfer of foreign exchange assets not to be charged in certain cases. —`
  line `( 1 ) Where, in the case of an assessee being a non-resident Indian, any long-term capital gains arise from`
  line `the transfer of a foreign exchange asset (the asset so transferred being hereafter in this section referred to`
  line `as the original asset), and the assessee has, within a period of six months after the date of such transfer,`
  line `invested 3 *** the whole or any part of the net consideration in any specified asset 4 ***, or in any savings`
  line `certificates referred to in clause ( 4B ) of section 10 (such specified asset 5 ***, or such savings certificates`
  line `being hereafter in this section referred to as the new asset), the capital gain shall be dealt with in`
  line `accordance with the following provisions of this section, that is to say, —`
  line `( a ) if the cost of the new asset is not less than the net consideration in respect of the original`
  line `asset, the whole of such capital gain shall not be charged under section 45;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 57, for “under sub -section ( 2 ) of section 48 or under Chapter VIA” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1993).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 36, for section 115E (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `3. The words “or deposited” omitted by Act 26 of 1988, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `4. The words, brackets, figure and letter “or in an account referred to in clause ( 4A )” omitted by s. 32, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-`
  line `1989).`
  line `5. The wo rds “or such deposit in the account aforesaid” omitted by s. 32, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
