  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_481_footnotes
  sourcePage 481
obj_root_law_sections_481_content:
  string
  line 481
  line `( b ) if the cost of the new asset is less than the net consideration in respect of the original asset, so`
  line `much of the capital gain as bears to the whole of the capital gain the same proportion as the cost of`
  line `acquisition of the new asset bears to the net consideration shall not be charged under section 45.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, —`
  line `( i ) “cost”, in relation to any new asset, being a deposit 1 *** referred to in sub-clause ( iii ), or`
  line `specified under sub-clause ( v ), of clause ( f ) of section 115C, means the amount of such deposit;`
  line `( ii ) “net consideration”, in relation to the transfer of the original asset, means the full value of the`
  line `consideration received or accruing as a result of the transfer of such asset as reduced by any`
  line `expenditure incurred wholly and exclusively in connection with such transfer.`
  line `( 2 ) Where the new asset is transferred or converted (otherwise than by transfer) into money, within a`
  line `period of three years from the date of its acquisition, the amount of capital gain arising from the transfer`
  line `of the original asset not charged under section 45 on the basis of the cost of such new asset as provided in`
  line `clause ( a ) or, as the case may be, clause ( b ), of sub-section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to be income chargeable`
  line `under the head “Capital gains” relatin g to capital assets other than short-term capital assets of the`
  line `previous year in which the new asset is transferred or converted (otherwise than by transfer) into money.`
  line `115G. Return of income not to be filed in certain cases. It shall not be necessary for a non-resident`
  line `Indian to furnish under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139 a return of his income if —`
  line `( a ) his total income in respect of which he is assessable under this Act during the previous year`
  line `consisted only of investment income or income by way of long-term capital gains or both; and`
  line `( b ) the tax deductible at source under the provisions of Chapter XVIIB has been deducted from`
  line `such income.`
  line `115H. Benefit under Chapter to be available in certain cases even after the assessee becomes`
  line `resident. — Where a person, who is a non-resident Indian in any previous year, becomes assessable as`
  line `resident in India in respect of the total income of any subsequent year, he may furnish to the 2 [Assessing`
  line `Officer] a declaration in writing along with his return of income under section 139 for the assessment year`
  line `for which he is so assessable, to the effect that the provisions of this Chapter shall continue to apply to`
  line `him in relation to the investment income derived from any foreign exchange asset being an asset of the`
  line `nature referred to in sub-clause ( ii ) or sub-clause ( iii ) or sub-clause ( iv ) or sub-clause ( v ) of clause ( f ) of`
  line `section 115C; and if he does so, the provisions of this Chapter shall continue to apply to him in relation to`
  line `such income for that assessment year and for every subsequent assessment year until the transfer or`
  line `conversion (otherwise than by transfer) into money of such assets.`
  line `115-I. Chapter not to apply if the assessee so chooses. — A non-resident Indian may elect not to be`
  line `governed by the provisions of this Chapter for any assessment year by furnishing his return of income for`
  line `that assessment year under section 139 declaring therein that the provisions of this Chapter shall not apply`
  line `to him for that assessment year and if he does so, the provisions of this Chapter shall not apply to him for`
  line `that assessment year and his total income for that assessment year shall be computed and tax on such total`
  line `income shall be charged in accordance with the other provisions of this Act.]`
  line `1. The words, brackets, figures and letter “referred to in clause ( 4A ) of section 10 or” omitted by Act 26 of 1988, s. 32`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
