obj_root_law_sections_484_content:
  string
  line 484
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, “book profit” means the net profit as shown in the`
  line `profit and loss account for the relevant previous year prepared under sub-section ( 2 ), as increased by —`
  line `( a ) the amount of income-tax paid or payable, and the provision therefor; or`
  line `( b ) the amounts carried to any reserves by whatever name called; or`
  line `( c ) the amount or amounts set aside to provisions made for meeting liabilities, other than`
  line `ascertained liabilities; or`
  line `( d ) the amount by way of provision for losses of subsidiary companies; or`
  line `( e ) the amount or amounts of dividends paid or proposed; or`
  line `( f ) the amount or amounts of expenditure relatable to any income to which any of the provisions`
  line `of Chapter III applies;`
  line `1 [( g ) the amount or amounts set aside as provision for diminution in the value of any asset,`
  line `if any amount referred to in clauses ( a ) to ( g ) is debited to the profit and loss account, and as reduced`
  line `by, — ]`
  line `( i ) the amount withdrawn from any reserves or provisions if any such amount is credited to the`
  line `profit and loss account:`
  line `Provided that, where this section is applicable to an assessee in any previous year (including the`
  line `relevant previous year), the amount withdrawn from reserves created or provisions made in a`
  line `previous year relevant to the assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 1997 2 [but`
  line `ending before the 1st day of April, 2001] shall not be reduced from the book profit unless the book`
  line `profit of such year has been increased by those reserves or provisions (out of which the said amount`
  line `was withdrawn) under this Explanation; or`
  line `( ii ) the amount of income to which any of the provisions of Chapter III applies, if any such`
  line `amount is credited to the profit and loss account; or`
  line `3 [( iii ) the amount of loss brought forward or unabsorbed depreciation, whichever is less as per`
  line `books of account.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( a ) the loss shall not include depreciation;`
  line `( b ) the provisions of this clause shall not apply if the amount of loss brought forward or`
  line `unabsorbed depreciation is nil; or]`
  line `( iv ) the amount of profits derived by an industrial undertaking from the business of generation or`
  line `generation and distribution of power; or`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 44, for “if any amount re ferred to in clauses ( a ) to ( f ) is debited to the profit and loss account,`
  line `and as reduced by, —” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1998).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 51, for “clause ( iii ) and the Explanation thereto” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1997).`
