obj_root_law_sections_485_content:
  string
  line 485
  line `( v ) the amount of profits derived by an industrial undertaking located in an industrially backward`
  line `State or district as referred to in 1 [sub-section ( 4 ) and sub-section ( 5 ) of section 80-IB], for the`
  line `assessment years such industrial undertaking is eligible to claim a deduction of hundred per cent of`
  line `the 2 [profits and gains under sub-section ( 4 ) or sub-section ( 5 ) of section 80-IB]; or`
  line `( vi ) the amount of profits derived by an industrial undertaking from the business of developing,`
  line `maintaining and operating any infrastructure facility 3 [as defined in the Explanation to sub-section ( 4 )`
  line `of section 80-IA and subject to fulfilling the conditions laid down in that sub-section]; or`
  line `( vii ) the amount of profits of sick industrial company for the assessment year commencing from`
  line `the assessment year relevant to the previous year in which the said company has become a sick`
  line `industrial company under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 17 of the Sick Industrial Companies (Special`
  line `Provisions) Act, 1985 (1 of 1986) and ending with the assessment year during which the entire net`
  line `worth of such company becomes equal to or exceeds the accumulated losses.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, “net worth” shall have the meaning assigned to it`
  line `in clause ( ga ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 3 of the Sick Industrial Companies (Special Provisions)`
  line `Act, 1985 (1 of 1986); 4 [or]`
  line `5 [( viii ) the amount of profits eligible for deduction under section 80HHC, computed under clause`
  line `( a ), ( b ) or ( c ) of sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 3A ), as the case may be, of that section, and subject to`
  line `the conditions specified in sub-sections ( 4 ) and ( 4A ) of that section;`
  line `( ix ) the amount of profits eligible for deduction under section 80HHE, computed under`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ) of that section.]`
  line `( 3 ) Nothing contained in sub-section ( 1 ) shall affect the determination of the amounts in relation to`
  line `the relevant previous year to be carried forward to the subsequent year or years under the provisions of`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 32 or sub-section ( 3 ) of section 32A or clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 72 or section 73 or section 74 or sub-section ( 3 ) of section 74A.`
  line `( 4 ) Save as otherwise provided in this section, all other provisions of this Act shall apply to every`
  line `assessee, being a company, mentioned in this section.]`
  line `6 [115JAA. Tax credit in respect of tax paid on deemed income relating to certain companies. — ( 1 )`
  line `Where any amount of tax is paid under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115JA by an assessee being a company`
  line `for any assessment year, then, credit in respect of tax so paid shall be allowed to him in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of this section.`
  line `7 [( 1A ) Where any amount of tax is paid under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115JB by an assessee, being a`
  line `company for the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 2006 and any subsequent`
  line `assessment year, then, credit in respect of tax so paid shall be allowed to him in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this section.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 90, for “sub -clause ( b ) or sub-clause ( c ) of clause ( iv ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 80- IA”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 90, ibid., for “profits and gains under sub -section ( 5 ) of section 80- IA” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2000).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 90, ibid., for “under sub -section ( 12 ) of section 80-IA, and subject to fulfilling the conditions laid down in`
  line `sub-section ( 4A ) of section 80- IA” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2000).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-1997).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 37, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 38 (w.e.f. 1-4-1997).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
