obj_root_law_sections_486_content:
  string
  line 486
  line `1 [( 2 ) The tax credit to be allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be the difference of the tax paid for any`
  line `assessment year under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115JA and the amount of tax payable by the assessee on`
  line `his total income computed in accordance with the other provisions of this Act:`
  line `Provided that no interest shall be payable on the tax credit allowed under sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 2A ) The tax credit to be allowed under sub-section ( 1A ) shall be the difference of the tax paid for any`
  line `assessment year under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115JB and the amount of tax payable by the assessee on`
  line `his total income computed in accordance with the other provisions of this Act:`
  line `Provided that no interest shall be payable on the tax credit allowed under sub-section ( 1A ):`
  line `2 [Provided further that where the amount of tax credit in respect of any income-tax paid in any country or`
  line `specified territory outside India, under section 90 or section 90A or section 91, allowed against the tax`
  line `payable under the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115JB exceeds the amount of such tax credit`
  line `admissible against the tax payable by the assessee on its income in accordance with the other provisions of`
  line `this Act, then, while computing the amount of credit under this sub-section, such excess amount shall be`
  line ignored.]
  line `( 3 ) The amount of tax credit determined under sub-section ( 2 ) shall be carried forward and set off in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of sub-sections ( 4 ) and ( 5 ) but such carry forward shall not be allowed`
  line `beyond the fifth assessment year immediately succeeding the assessment year in which tax credit`
  line `becomes allowable under sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 3A ) The amount of tax credit determined under sub-section ( 2A ) shall be carried forward and set off`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of sub-sections ( 4 ) and ( 5 ) but such carry forward shall not be allowed`
  line `beyond the 3 [fifteenth assessment year] immediately succeeding the assessment year in which tax credit`
  line `becomes allowable under sub-section ( 1A ).]`
  line `( 4 ) The tax credit shall be allowed set-off in a year when tax becomes payable on the total income`
  line `computed in accordance with the provisions of this Act other than section 115JA 4 [or section 115JB, as`
  line `the case may be].`
  line `( 5 ) Set off in respect of brought forward tax credit shall be allowed for any assessment year to the`
  line `extent of the difference between the tax on his total income and the tax which would have been payable`
  line `under the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115JA 4 [or section 115JB, as the case may be] for that`
  line `assessment year.`
  line `( 6 ) Where as a result of an order under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 3 ) of section 143,`
  line `section 144, section 147, section 154, section 155, sub-section ( 4 ) of section 245D, section 250,`
  line `section 254, section 260, section 262, section 263 or section 264, the amount of tax payable under this`
  line `Act is reduced or increased, as the case may be, the amount of tax credit allowed under this section shall`
  line `also be increased or reduced accordingly.`
  line `5 [( 7 ) In case of conversion of a private company or unlisted public company into a limited liability`
  line `partnership under the Limited Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009), the provisions of this section`
  line `shall not apply to the successor limited liability partnership.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, the expressi ons “private company” and “unlisted`
  line `public company” shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in the Limited Liability`
  line `Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009).]]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 23, for sub-sections ( 2 ) and ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 46 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `3. Subs. by, s. 46, ibid., for “tenth assessment year” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2018).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 51 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-2011).`
