obj_root_law_sections_487_content:
  string
  line 487
  line `1 [115JB. Special provision for payment of tax by certain companies. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in any other provision of this Act, where in the case of an assessee, being a company,`
  line `the income-tax, payable on the total income as computed under this Act in respect of any previous year`
  line `relevant to the assessment year commencing on or after 2 [the 1st day of April, 2012], is less than`
  line `3 [eighteen and one-half per cent.] of its book profit, 4 [such book profit shall be deemed to be the total`
  line `income of the assessee and the tax payable by the assessee on such total income shall be the amount of`
  line `income-tax at the rate of 3 [eighteen and one-half per cent.]].`
  line `( 2 ) 5 [Every assessee, —`
  line `( a ) being a company, other than a company referred to in clause ( b ), shall, for the purposes of this`
  line `section, prepare its 6 [statement of profit and loss] for the relevant previous year in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of 7 [Schedule III] to 8 [the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)]; or`
  line `( b ) being a company, to which the 9 [second proviso to sub-section ( 1 ) of section 129] of 8 [the`
  line `Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)] is applicable, shall, for the purposes of this section, prepare its`
  line `6 [statement of profit and loss] for the relevant previous year in accordance with the provisions of the`
  line `Act governing such company:]`
  line `Provided that while preparing the annual accounts including 6 [statement of profit and loss], —`
  line `( i ) the accounting policies;`
  line `( ii ) the accounting standards adopted for preparing such accounts including 6 [statement of`
  line `profit and loss;`
  line `( iii ) the method and rates adopted for calculating the depreciation,`
  line `shall be the same as have been adopted for the purpose of preparing such accounts including`
  line `6 [statement of profit and loss] and laid before the company at its annual general meeting in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of 10 [section 210] of 8 [the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)]:`
  line `Provided further that where the company has adopted or adopts the financial year under 8 [the`
  line `Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)], which is different from the previous year under this Act, —`
  line `( i ) the accounting policies;`
  line `( ii ) the accounting standards adopted for preparing such accounts including 6 [statement of`
  line `profit and loss];`
  line `( iii ) the method and rates adopted for calculating the depreciation,`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 52 (w.e.f. 1-4-2001).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 18, for “the 1st day of April, 2011” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2012).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for “eighteen per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2012).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 52, for “the tax payable for the relevant previous year shall be dee med to be seven and one-`
  line `half per cent. of such book profit” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2001).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 48, for the portion beginning with the words “Every assessee,” and ending with the words and`
  line `figures “the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956):” (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 47, for “profit and loss account” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 47, ibid., for “Part II of Schedule VI” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 47, ibid., for “the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `9. Subs. by s. 47, ibid., for “proviso to sub -section ( 2 ) of section 211” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `10. Subs. by s. 47, ibid., for “section 210” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
