obj_root_law_sections_492_content:
  string
  line 492
  line `( b ) decreased by all amounts debited to other comprehensive income in the statement of profit`
  line `and loss under the head “Items that will not be re -classified to profit or loss;`
  line `( c ) increased by amounts or aggregate of the amounts debited to the statement of profit and loss`
  line `on distribution of non-cash assets to shareholders in a demerger in accordance with Appendix A of`
  line `the Indian Accounting Standards 10;`
  line `( d ) decreased by all amounts or aggregate of the amounts credited to the statement of profit and`
  line `loss on distribution of non-cash assets to shareholders in a demerger in accordance with Appendix A`
  line `of the Indian Accounting Standards 10:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) shall apply to the amount credited or`
  line `debited to other comprehensive income under the head “Items that will not be re-classified to profit or`
  line `loss” in respect of —`
  line `( i ) revaluation surplus for assets in accordance with the Indian Accounting Standards 16 and`
  line `Indian Accounting Standards 38; or`
  line `( ii ) gains or losses from investments in equity instruments designated at fair value through`
  line `other comprehensive income in accordance with the Indian Accounting Standards 109:`
  line `Provided further that the book profit of the previous year in which the asset or investment`
  line `referred to in the first proviso is retired, disposed, realised or otherwise transferred shall be`
  line `increased or decreased, as the case may be, by the amount or the aggregate of the amounts`
  line `referred to in the first proviso for the previous year or any of the preceding previous years and`
  line `relatable to such asset or investment.`
  line `( 2B ) In the case of a resulting company, where the property and the liabilities of the undertaking or`
  line `undertakings being received by it are recorded at values different from values appearing in the books of`
  line `account of the demerged company immediately before the demerger, any change in such value shall be`
  line `ignored for the purpose of computation of book profit of the resulting company under this section.`
  line `( 2C ) For a company referred to in sub-section ( 2A ), the book profit of the year of convergence and`
  line `each of the following four previous years, shall be further increased or decreased, as the case may be, by`
  line `one-fifth of the transition amount:`
  line `Provided that the book profit of the previous year in which the asset or investment referred to in`
  line `sub-clauses ( B ) to ( E ) of clause ( iii ) of the Explanation is retired, disposed, realised or otherwise`
  line `transferred, shall be increased or decreased, as the case may be, by the amount or the aggregate of the`
  line `amounts referred to in the said sub-clauses relatable to such asset or investment:`
  line `Provided further that the book profit of the previous year in which the foreign operation referred to in`
  line `sub-clause ( F ) of clause ( iii ) of the Explanation is disposed or otherwise transferred, shall be increased or`
  line `decreased, as the case may be, by the amount or the aggregate of the amounts referred to in the said`
  line `sub-clauses relatable to such foreign operations.`
  line `Explanation. –– For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression ––`
  line `( i ) “year of convergence” means the previous year within which the convergence date falls;`
  line `( ii ) “convergence date” means the first day of the first Indian Accounting Standards reporting`
  line `period as defined in the Indian Accounting Standards 101;`
  line `( iii ) “transition amount” means the amount or the aggregate of the amounts adjusted in the other`
  line `equity (excluding capital reserve and securities premium reserve) on the convergence date but not`
  line `including the following: ––`
  line `( A ) amount or aggregate of the amounts adjusted in the other comprehensive income on the`
  line `convergence date which shall be subsequently re-classified to the profit or loss;`
  line `( B ) revaluation surplus for assets in accordance with the Indian Accounting Standards 16 and`
  line `Indian Accounting Standards 38 adjusted on the convergence date;`
