obj_root_law_sections_494_content:
  string
  line 494
  line `1 [CHAPTER XIIBA`
  line `S PECIAL PROVISIONS RELATING TO CERTAIN 2 [ PERSONS OTHER THAN A COMPANY ]`
  line `3 [ 115JC. Special provisions for payment of tax by certain persons other than a company. — ( 1 )`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, where the regular income-tax payable for a previous year`
  line `by a person, other than a company, is less than the alternate minimum tax payable for such previous year,`
  line `the adjusted total income shall be deemed to be the total income of that person for such previous year and`
  line `he shall be liable to pay income-tax on such total income at the rate of eighteen and one-half per cent.`
  line `( 2 ) Adjusted total income referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be the total income before giving effect`
  line `to this Chapter as increased by —`
  line `( i ) deductions claimed, if any, under any section (other than section 80P) included in`
  line `Chapter VIA under the heading ”C.— Deductions in respect of certain incomes ”; 4 ***`
  line `( ii ) deduction claimed, if any, 5 [under section 10AA; and]`
  line `6 [( iii ) deduction claimed, if any, under section 35AD as reduced by the amount of depreciation`
  line `allowable in accordance with the provisions of section 32 as if no deduction under section 35AD was`
  line `allowed in respect of the assets on which the deduction under that section is claimed.]`
  line `( 3 ) Every person to whom this section applies shall obtain a report, in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed, from an accountant, certifying that the adjusted total income and the alternate minimum tax`
  line `have been computed in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter and furnish such report on or`
  line `before the due date of furnishing of return of income under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139. ]`
  line `7 [( 4 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), where the person referred to therein, is a`
  line `unit located in an International Financial Services Centre and derives its income solely in convertible`
  line `foreign exchange, the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) shall have effect as if for the words “eighteen and one -`
  line `half per cent.”, the words “nine per cent.” had been substituted. ]`
  line `115JD. Tax credit for alternate minimum tax. — ( 1 ) The credit for tax paid by 8 [a person`
  line `under section 115JC shall be allowed to him] in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line `( 2 ) The tax credit of an assessment year to be allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be the excess of`
  line `alternate minimum tax paid over the regular income-tax payable of that year.`
  line `9 [Provided that where the amount of tax credit in respect of any income-tax paid in any country or`
  line `specified territory outside India under section 90 or section 90A or section 91, allowed against the alternate`
  line `minimum tax payable, exceeds the amount of the tax credit admissible against the regular income-tax`
  line `payable by the assessee, then, while computing the amount of credit under this sub-section, such excess`
  line `amount shall be ignored.]`
  line `( 3 ) No interest shall be payable on tax credit allowed under sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-2012).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 49, for “LIMITED LIABILITY PARTERSHIPS” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 50, ibid., for section 115JC (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `4. The “word” omitted by Act 25 of 2014, s. 39 (w.e.f. 1 -4-2015).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 39, ibid., for “under section 10AA” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2015).`
  line `6. Ins. by s. 39, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 38 (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 51, for “a limited liability partnership under section 115JC shall be allowed to it”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 48 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
