obj_root_law_sections_495_content:
  string
  line 495
  line `( 4 ) The amount of tax credit determined under sub-section ( 2 ) shall be carried forward and set off in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of sub-sections ( 5 ) and ( 6 ) but such carry forward shall not be allowed`
  line `beyond the 1 [fifteenth assessment year] immediately succeeding the assessment year for which tax credit`
  line `becomes allowable under sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 5 ) In any assessment year in which the regular income-tax exceeds the alternate minimum tax, the`
  line `tax credit shall be allowed to be set off to the extent of the excess of regular income-tax over the alternate`
  line `minimum tax and the balance of the tax credit, if any, shall be carried forward.`
  line `( 6 ) If the amount of regular income-tax or the alternate minimum tax is reduced or increased as a`
  line `result of any order passed under this Act, the amount of tax credit allowed under this section shall also be`
  line `varied accordingly.`
  line `115JE. Application of other provisions of this Act. — Save as otherwise provided in this Chapter,`
  line `all other provisions of this Act shall apply to a 2 [person] referred to in this Chapter.`
  line `3 [ 115JEE. Application of this Chapter to certain persons. — ( 1 ) The provisions of this Chapter`
  line `shall apply to a person who has claimed any deduction under —`
  line `( a ) any section (other than section 80P) included in Chapter VI-A under the heading ”C.—`
  line `Deductions in respect of certain incomes ”; or`
  line `4 [( b ) section 10AA; or`
  line `( c ) section 35AD.]`
  line `( 2 ) The provisions of this Chapter shall not apply to an individual or a Hindu undivided family or an`
  line `association of persons or a body of individuals, whether incorporated or not, or an artificial juridical`
  line `person referred to in sub-clause ( vii ) of clause ( 31 ) of section 2, if the adjusted total income of such`
  line `person does not exceed twenty lakh rupees.]`
  line `5 [( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ), the credit for tax paid`
  line `under section 115JC shall be allowed in accordance with the provisions of section 115JD.]`
  line `115JF. Interpretation in this Chapter. In this Chapter —`
  line `( a ) “accountant” shall have the same meaning as in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 288;`
  line `6 [( b ) “alternate minimum tax” means the amount of tax computed on adjusted total income,––`
  line `( i ) in case of an assessee being a unit referred to in sub-section ( 4 ) of section 115JC, at a rate`
  line `of nine per cent.;`
  line `( ii ) in any other case, at a rate of eighteen and one-half per cent.;]`
  line `7 [( ba ) “convertible foreign exchange” means a foreign exchange which is for the time being`
  line `treated by the Reserve Bank of India as convertible foreign exchange for the purpose of the Foreign`
  line `Exchange Management Act, 1999 and the rules made thereunder;`
  line `( bb ) “International Financial Services Centre” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( q )`
  line `of section 2 of the Special Economic Zones Act, 2005;]`
  line `8 * * * * *`
  line `1. Subs. by Ac t 7 of 2017, s. 48, for “tenth assessment year” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2018).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 52, for “a limited liability partnership” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 53, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 40, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 40, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 39, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f.1-4-2019).`
  line `7. Ins. by s. 39, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2019).`
  line `8. Clause ( c ) omitted by Act 23 of 2012, s. 54 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
