obj_root_law_sections_496_content:
  string
  line 496
  line `( d ) “regular income - tax” means the income-tax payable for a previous year by 1 [a person on his`
  line `total income] in accordance with the provisions of this Act other than the provisions of this Chapter.]`
  line `2 [( e ) “unit” means a unit established in an International Financial Services Centre.]`
  line `3 [CHAPTER XIIBB`
  line `S PECIAL PROVISIONS RELATING TO CONVERSION OF I NDIAN BRANCH OF A FOREIGN BANK INTO A`
  line `SUBSIDIARY COMPANY`
  line `115JG. Conversion of an Indian branch of foreign company into subsidiary Indian`
  line `company. — ( 1 ) Where a foreign company is engaged in the business of banking in India through its`
  line `branch situate in India and such branch is converted into a subsidiary company thereof, being an Indian`
  line `company (hereafter referred to as an Indian subsidiary company) in accordance with the scheme framed`
  line `by the Reserve Bank of India, then, notwithstanding anything contained in the Act and subject to the`
  line `conditions as may be notified by the Central Government in this behalf, —`
  line `( i ) the capital gains arising from such conversion shall not be chargeable to tax in the assessment`
  line `year relevant to the previous year in which such conversion takes place;`
  line `( ii ) the provisions of this Act relating to treatment of unabsorbed depreciation, set off or carry`
  line `forward and set off of losses, tax credit in respect of tax paid on deemed income relating to certain`
  line `companies and the computation of income in the case of the foreign company and Indian subsidiary`
  line `company shall apply with such exceptions, modifications and adaptations as may be specified in that`
  line notification.
  line `( 2 ) In case of failure to comply with any of the conditions specified in the scheme or in the`
  line `notification issued under sub-section ( 1 ), all the provisions of this Act shall apply to the foreign company`
  line `and the said Indian subsidiary company without any benefit, exemption or relief under sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 3 ) Where, in a previous year, any benefit, exemption or relief has been claimed and granted to the`
  line `foreign company or the Indian subsidiary company in accordance with the provisions of sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `and, subsequently, there is failure to comply with any of the conditions specified in the scheme or in the`
  line `notification issued under sub-section ( 1 ), then, —`
  line `( i ) such benefit, exemption or relief shall be deemed to have been wrongly allowed;`
  line `( ii ) the Assessing Officer may, notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, re-compute the`
  line `total income of the assessee for the said previous year and make the necessary amendment; and`
  line `( iii ) the provisions of section 154 shall, so far as may be, apply thereto and the period of four`
  line `years specified in sub-section ( 7 ) of that section being reckoned from the end of the previous year in`
  line `which the failure to comply with the condition referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) takes place.`
  line `( 4 ) Every notification issued under this section shall be laid before each House of Parliament.]`
  line `4 [CHAPTER XIIBC`
  line `S PECIAL PROVISIONS RELATING TO FOREIGN COMPANY SAID TO BE RESIDENT IN INDIA`
  line `115JH. Foreign company said to be resident in India. — ( 1 ) Where a foreign company is said to be`
  line `resident in India in any previ- ous year and such foreign company has not been resident in India in any of`
  line `the previous years preceding the said previous year, then, notwithstanding anything contained in this Act`
  line `and subject to the conditions as may be notified by the Central Government in this behalf, the provisions`
  line `of this Act relating to the computation of total income, treatment of unabsorbed depreciation, set off or`
  line `carry forward and set off of losses, collection and recovery and special provisions relating to avoidance of`
  line `tax shall apply with such exceptions, modifications and adaptations as may be specified in that`
  line `notification for the said previous year:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 54, for “a limited liability partnership on its total income” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 39 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 55 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 56 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_496_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_497:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-497
  sectionNo (497)
  orderNo 497
  title `Page 497`
  content obj_root_law_sections_497_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_497_footnotes
  sourcePage 497
obj_root_law_sections_497_content:
  string
  line 497
  line `Provided that where the determination regarding foreign company to be resident in India has been`
  line `made in the assessment proceedings relevant to any previous year, then, the provisions of this sub-section`
  line `shall also apply in respect of any other previous year, succeeding such previous year, if the foreign`
  line `company is resident in India in that previous year and the previous year ends on or before the date on`
  line `which such assessment proceeding is completed.`
  line `( 2 ) Where, in a previous year, any benefit, exemption or relief has been claimed and granted to the`
  line `foreign company in accordance with the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ), and, subsequently, there is failure`
  line `to comply with any of the conditions specified in the notification issued under sub-section ( 1 ), then, —`
  line `( i ) such benefit, exemption or relief shall be deemed to have been wrongly allowed;`
  line `( ii ) the Assessing Officer may, notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, re-compute the`
  line `total income of the assessee for the said previous year and make the necessary amendment as if the`
  line `exceptions, modifications and adaptations referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) did not apply; and`
  line `( iii ) the provisions of section 154 shall, so far as may be, apply thereto and the period of four`
  line `years specified in sub-section ( 7 ) of that section being reckoned from the end of the previous year in`
  line `which the failure to comply with the condition referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) takes place.`
  line `( 3 ) Every notification issued under this section shall be laid before each House of Parliament.]`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `115K. [ Special provision for computation of income in certain cases. ] — Omitted by the Finance`
  line `Act 1997 (26 of 1997), s. 39 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `115L. [Return of income not to be filed in certain cases.] — Omitted by the Finance`
  line `Act, 1997 (26 of 1997), s. 39 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `115M. [ Special provision for disallowance of deductions and rebate of income-tax.] — Omitted by`
  line `the Finance Act, 1997 (26 of 1997), s. 39, ( w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `115N. [Bar of proceedings in certain cases. ] — Omitted by the Finance Act, 1997 (26 of 1997), s. 39,`
  line `( w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `2 [CHAPTER XIID`
  line `S PECIAL PROVISIONS RELATING TO TAX ON DISTRIBUTED PROFITS OF DOMESTIC COMPANIES`
  line `115-O. Tax on distributed profits of domestic companies. — 3 [( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other provision of this Act and subject to the provisions of this section, in addition to the`
  line `income-tax chargeable in respect of the total income of a domestic company for any assessment year, any`
  line `amount declared, distributed or paid by such company by way of dividends (whether interim or`
  line `otherwise) on or after the 1st day of April, 2003, whether out of current or accumulated profits shall be`
  line `charged to additional income-tax (hereafter referred to as tax on distributed profits) 4 [at the rate of fifteen`
  line `per cent.]]`
  line `5 [Provided that in respect of dividend referred to in sub-clause ( e ) of clause ( 22 ) of section 2, this`
  line `sub- section shall have effect as if for the words “fifteen per cent.”, the words “thirty per cent.” had been`
  line substituted;]
  line `1. Chapter XIIC consisting of sections 115K to 115N omitted by Act 26 of 1997, s. 39 (w.e.f. 1-4-1998). Earlier Chapter`
  line `XIIC was inserted by the Act 18 of 1992, s. 58 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 40, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-1997).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 55, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2003). Earlier sub-section ( 1 ) was amended by Act 10 of`
  line `2000, s. 53 (w.e.f. 1-6-2000), Act 14 of 2001, s. 55 (w.e.f. 1-6-2001), and Act 20 of 2002, s. 53 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 35, for “at the rate of twelve and one- half per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2007).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
