obj_root_law_sections_498_content:
  string
  line 498
  line `1 [( 1A ) The amount referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be reduced by, —`
  line `2 [( i ) the amount of dividend, if any, received by the domestic company during the financial year,`
  line `if such dividend is received from its subsidiary and, —`
  line `( a ) where such subsidiary is a domestic company, the subsidiary has paid the tax which is`
  line `payable under this section on such dividend; or`
  line `( b ) where such subsidiary is a foreign company, the tax is payable by the domestic company`
  line `under section 115BBD on such dividend:`
  line `Provided that the same amount of dividend shall not be taken into account for reduction more`
  line `than once;]`
  line `( ii ) the amount of dividend, if any, paid to any person for, or on behalf of, the New Pension`
  line `System Trust referred to in clause ( 44 ) of section 10.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, a company shall be a subsidiary of another`
  line `company, if such other company, holds more than half in nominal value of the equity share capital of the`
  line company.]
  line `3 [( 1B ) For the purposes of determining the tax on distributed profits payable in accordance with this`
  line `section, any amount by way of dividends referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) as reduced by the amount referred`
  line `to in sub-section ( 1A ) [hereafter referred to as net distributed profits], shall be increased to such amount`
  line `as would, after reduction of the tax on such increased amount at the rate specified in sub-section ( 1 ), be`
  line `equal to the net distributed profits.]`
  line `4 [Provided that this sub-section shall not apply in respect of dividend referred to in sub-clause (e) of`
  line `clause (22) of section 2.]`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding that no income-tax is payable by a domestic company on its total income`
  line `computed in accordance with the provisions of this Act, the tax on distributed profits under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) shall be payable by such company.`
  line `( 3 ) The principal officer of the domestic company and the company shall be liable to pay the tax on`
  line `distributed profits to the credit of the Central Government within fourteen days from the date of —`
  line `( a ) declaration of any dividend; or`
  line `( b ) distribution of any dividend; or`
  line `( c ) payment of any dividend,`
  line `whichever is earliest.`
  line `( 4 ) The tax on distributed profits so paid by the company shall be treated as the final payment of tax`
  line `in respect of the amount declared, distributed or paid as dividends and no further credit therefor shall be`
  line `claimed by the company or by any other person in respect of the amount of tax so paid.`
  line `( 5 ) No deduction under any other provision of this Act shall be allowed to the company or a`
  line `shareholder in respect of the amount which has been charged to tax under sub-section ( 1 ) or the tax`
  line thereon.
  line `5 [( 6 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, no tax on distributed profits shall be`
  line `chargeable in respect of the total income of an undertaking or enterprise engaged in developing or`
  line `developing and operating or developing, operating and maintaining a Special Economic Zone for any`
  line `assessment year on any amount declared, distributed or paid by such Developer or enterprise, by way of`
  line `dividends (whether interim or otherwise) on or after the 1st day of April, 2005 out of its current income`
  line `either in the hands of the Developer or enterprise or the person receiving such dividend 6 *** ]:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 47, for sub-section ( 1A ) (w.r.e.f. (1-4-2009). Earlier sub-section ( 1A ) was inserted by`
  line `Act 18 of 2008, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 30, for clause ( i ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 28 of 2005, s. 27 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 10-2-2006).`
  line `6. The words “not falling under clause ( 23G )” omitted by Act 21 of 2006, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1 -4-2007).`
