obj_root_law_sections_499_content:
  string
  line 499
  line `1 [Provided that the provisions of this sub-section shall cease to have effect from the 1st day of June,`
  line 2011.]
  line `2 [( 7 ) No tax on distributed profits shall be chargeable under this section in respect of any amount`
  line `declared, distributed or paid by the specified domestic company by way of dividends (whether interim or`
  line `otherwise) to a business trust out of its current income on or after the specified date:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply in respect of any amount declared,`
  line `distributed or paid, at any time, by the specified domestic company by way of dividends (whether interim`
  line `or otherwise) out of its accumulated profits and current profits up to the specified date.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, —`
  line `( a ) “specified domestic company” means a domestic compan y in which a business trust has`
  line `become the holder of whole of the nominal value of equity share capital of the company (excluding`
  line `the equity share capital required to be held mandatorily by any other person in accordance with any`
  line `law for the time being in force or any directions of Government or any regulatory authority, or equity`
  line `share capital held by any Government or Government body);`
  line `( b ) “specified date” means the date of acquisition by the business trust of such holding as is`
  line `referred to in clause ( a ).]`
  line `3 [( 8 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, no tax on distributed profits shall be`
  line `chargeable in respect of the total income of a company, being a unit of an International Financial Services`
  line `Centre, deriving income solely in convertible foreign exchange, for any assessment year on any amount`
  line `declared, distributed or paid by such company, by way of dividends (whether interim or otherwise) on or`
  line `after the 1st day of April, 2017, out of its current income, either in the hands of the company or the person`
  line `receiving such dividend.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, —`
  line `( a ) “International Financial Services Centre” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in`
  line `clause ( q ) of section 2 of the Special Economic Zones Act, 2005 (28 of 2005);`
  line `( b ) “unit” means a unit established in an International Financial Services Centre, on or after the`
  line `1st day of April, 2016;`
  line `( c ) “convertible foreign exchange” means foreign exchange which is for the time being treated`
  line `by the Reserve Bank of India as convertible foreign exchange for the purposes of the Foreign`
  line `Exchange Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999) and the rules made thereunder.]`
  line `115P. Interest payable for non-payment of tax by domestic companies. — Where the principal`
  line `officer of a domestic company and the company fails to pay the whole or any part of the tax on`
  line `distributed profits referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115-O, within the time allowed under sub-`
  line `section ( 3 ) of that section, he or it shall be liable to pay simple interest at the rate of 4 [one per cent.] for`
  line `every month or part thereof on the amount of such tax for the period beginning on the date immediately`
  line `after the last date on which such tax was payable and ending with the date on which the tax is actually`
  line paid.
  line `115Q. When company is deemed to be in default. — If any principal officer of a domestic company`
  line `and the company does not pay tax on distributed profits in accordance with the provisions of section`
  line `115O, then, he or it shall be deemed to be an assessee in default in respect of the amount of tax payable`
  line `by him or it and all the provisions of this Act for the collection and recovery of income-tax shall apply.`
  line `5 * * * * *]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-6-2011).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 57 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 57, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 4, for “one and one - fourth per cent.” (w.e.f. 8 -9-2003). Earlier the quoted words were`
  line `amended by Act 10 of 2000, s. 54 (w.e.f. 1-6-2000).`
  line `5. The Explanation omitted by Act 13 of 2018, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
