obj_root_law_sections_500_content:
  string
  line 500
  line `1 [CHAPTER XIIDA`
  line `S PECIAL PROVISIONS RELATING TO TAX ON DISTRIBUTED INCOME OF DOMESTIC COMPANY FOR BUY-BACK`
  line `OF SHARES`
  line `115QA. Tax on distributed income to shareholders. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `any other provision of this Act, in addition to the income-tax chargeable in respect of the total income of`
  line `a domestic company for any assessment year, any amount of distributed income by the company on buy-`
  line `back of shares (not being shares listed on a recognised stock exchange) from a shareholder shall be`
  line `charged to tax and such company shall be liable to pay additional income-tax at the rate of twenty per`
  line `cent on the distributed income.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) ”buy - back” means purchase by a company of its own shares in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of 2 [any law for the time being in force relating to companies];`
  line `( ii ) “distributed income” means the consideration paid by the company on buy -back of shares as`
  line `reduced by 3 [the amount, which was received by the company for issue of such shares, determined in`
  line `the manner as may be prescribed].`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding that no income-tax is payable by a domestic company on its total income`
  line `computed in accordance with the provisions of this Act, the tax on the distributed income under sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ) shall be payable by such company.`
  line `( 3 ) The principal officer of the domestic company and the company shall be liable to pay the tax to`
  line `the credit of the Central Government within fourteen days from the date of payment of any consideration`
  line `to the shareholder on buy-back of shares referred to in sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 4 ) The tax on the distributed income by the company shall be treated as the final payment of tax in`
  line `respect of the said income and no further credit therefor shall be claimed by the company or by any other`
  line `person in respect of the amount of tax so paid.`
  line `( 5 ) No deduction under any other provision of this Act shall be allowed to the company or a`
  line `shareholder in respect of the income which has been charged to tax under sub-section ( 1 ) or the tax`
  line thereon.
  line `115QB. Interest payable for non-payment of tax by company. — Where the principal officer of the`
  line `domestic company and the company fails to pay the whole or any part of the tax on the distributed income`
  line `referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115QA, within the time allowed under sub-section ( 3 ) of that`
  line `section, he or it shall be liable to pay simple interest at the rate of one per cent for every month or part`
  line `thereof on the amount of such tax for the period beginning on the date immediately after the last date on`
  line `which such tax was payable and ending with the date on which the tax is actually paid.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 58, for “section 77A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of1956)” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2016).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 58, ibid., for “the amount, which was received by the company for issue of such shares, determined in the`
  line `manner as may be prescribed” (1 -6-2016).`
