obj_root_law_sections_501_content:
  string
  line 501
  line `115QC. When company is deemed to be assessee in default. — If any principal officer of a`
  line `domestic company and the company does not pay tax on distributed income in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of section 115QA, then, he or it shall be deemed to be an assessee in default in respect of the`
  line `amount of tax payable by him or it and all the provisions of this Act for the collection and recovery of`
  line `income-tax shall apply.]`
  line `1 [CHAPTER XIIE`
  line `S PECIAL PROVISIONS RELATING TO TAX ON DISTRIBUTED INCOME`
  line `115R. Tax on distributed income to unit holders. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `other provisions of this Act and section 32 of the Unit Trust of India Act, 1963 (52 of 1963), 2 [any`
  line `amount of income distributed on or before the 31st day of March, 2002 by the Unit Trust of India to its`
  line `unit holders] shall be chargeable to tax and the Unit Trust of India shall be liable to pay additional`
  line `income-tax on such distributed income at the rate of 3 [ten per cent]:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply in respect of any income distributed to`
  line `a unit holder of open-ended equity oriented funds in respect of any distribution made from such fund for a`
  line `period of three years commencing from the 1st day of April, 1999.`
  line `4 [( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, any amount of income`
  line `distributed by the specified company or a Mutual Fund to its unit holders shall be chargeable to tax and`
  line `such specified company or Mutual Fund shall be liable to pay additional income-tax on such distributed`
  line `income 5 [at the rate of —`
  line `6 [( i ) twenty-five per cent. on income distributed to any person being an individual or a Hindu`
  line `undivided family by a money market mutual fund or a liquid fund;`
  line `( ii ) thirty per cent. on income distributed to any other person by a money market mutual fund or a`
  line `liquid fund;`
  line `( iii ) ten per cent. on income distributed to any person by an equity oriented fund;`
  line `( iv ) twenty-five per cent. on income distributed to any person being an individual or a Hindu`
  line `undivided family by a fund other than a money market mutual fund or a liquid fund or an equity`
  line `oriented fund; and`
  line `( v ) thirty per cent. on income distributed to any other person by a fund other than a money market`
  line `mutual fund or a liquid fund or an equity oriented fund:]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 61 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 54, for “any amount of income distributed on or before the 31st day of March, 2002 by the`
  line `Unit Trust of India to its unit holders” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2003).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 57, for “twenty per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2001), earlier substituted by Act 10 of 2000, s. 55 (w.e.f.`
  line `1-6-2001).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 56, for sub-section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2003), Earlier amended by 20 of 2002, s. 54 (w.e.f. 1-4-`
  line `2003).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 29, for “at the rate of twelve and one - half per cent.” (w.e.f. 9 -7-2004).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 42, for clause ( i ) to clause ( iii ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2018). Earlier it was amended by Act 17 of 2013,`
  line `s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-6-2013), Act 8 of 2011, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-6-2011) and Act 22 of 2007, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
