obj_root_law_sections_502_content:
  string
  line 502
  line `1 [Provided that where any income is distributed by a mutual fund under an infrastructure debt fund`
  line `scheme to a non-resident (not being a company) or a foreign company, the mutual fund shall be liable to`
  line `pay additional income-tax at the rate of five per cent on income so distributed:]`
  line `2 [Provided further that] nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply in respect of any income`
  line `distributed, —`
  line `( a ) by the Administrator of the specified undertaking, to the unit holders; or`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, —`
  line `( i ) “administrator” and “specified company” shall have the meanings respectively assigned to`
  line `them in the Explanation to clause ( 35 ) of section 10;`
  line `( ii ) “infrastructure debt fund scheme” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in cla use`
  line `( 1 ) of regulation 49L of the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Mutual Funds) Regulations,`
  line `1996 made under the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992).]`
  line `5 [( 2A ) For the purposes of determining the additional income-tax payable in accordance with sub-`
  line `section ( 2 ), the amount of distributed income referred therein shall be increased to such amount as would,`
  line `after reduction of the additional income-tax on such increased amount at the rate specified in sub-section`
  line `( 2 ), be equal to the amount of income distributed by the Mutual Fund.]`
  line `( 3 ) The person responsible for making payment of the income distributed by the Unit Trust of India`
  line `or a Mutual Fund and the Unit Trust of India or the Mutual Fund, as the case may be, shall be liable to`
  line `pay tax to the credit of the Central Government within fourteen days from the date of distribution or`
  line `payment of such income, whichever is earlier.`
  line `6 * * * *`
  line `( 4 ) No deduction under any other provision of this Act shall be allowed to the Unit Trust of India or`
  line `to a Mutual Fund in respect of the income which has been charged to tax under sub-section ( 1 ) or`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ).`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 32, ibid., for “Provided that” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `3. Clause ( b ) omitted by Act 13 of 2018, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018). Earlier it was amended by Act 21 of 2006,`
  line `s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-6-2006).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 32, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `6. Sub-section ( 3A ) omitted by s. 42, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).Earlier inserted by Act 10 of 2000, s. 55 (w.e.f. 1-6-2000).`
