obj_root_law_sections_504_content:
  string
  line 504
  line `1 [CHAPTER XIIEA`
  line `S PECIAL PROVISIONS RELATING TO TAX ON DISTRIBUTED`
  line `INCOME BY SECURITISATION TRUSTS`
  line `115TA. Tax on distributed income to investors. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `other provisions of the Act, any amount of income distributed by the securitisation trust to its investors`
  line `shall be chargeable to tax and such securitisation trust shall be liable to pay additional income-tax on such`
  line `distributed income at the rate of —`
  line `( i ) twenty-five per cent. on income distributed to any person being an individual or a Hindu`
  line `undivided family;`
  line `( ii ) thirty per cent. on income distributed to any other person:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply in respect of any income`
  line `distributed by the securitisation trust to any person in whose case income, irrespective of its nature`
  line `and source, is not chargeable to tax under the Act.`
  line `( 2 ) The person responsible for making payment of the income distributed by the securitisation trust`
  line `shall be liable to pay tax to the credit of the Central Government within fourteen days from the date of`
  line `distribution or payment of such income, whichever is earlier.`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `( 4 ) No deduction under any other provisions of this Act shall be allowed to the securitisation trust in`
  line `respect of the income which has been charged to tax under sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `3 [ ( 5 ) Nothing contained in this section shall apply in respect of any income distributed by a`
  line `securitisation trust to its investors on or after the 1st day of June, 2016. ]`
  line `115TB. Interest payable for non-payment of tax. — Where the person responsible for making`
  line `payment of the income distributed by the securitisation trust and the securitisation trust fails to pay the`
  line `whole or any part of the tax referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115TA, within the time allowed under`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of that section, he or it shall be liable to pay simple interest at the rate of one per cent.`
  line `every month or part thereof on the amount of such tax for the period beginning on the date immediately`
  line `after the last date on which such tax was payable and ending with the date on which the tax is actually`
  line paid.
  line `115TC. Securitisation trust to be assessee in default. — If any person responsible for making`
  line `payment of the income distributed by the securitisation trust and the securitisation trust does not pay tax,`
  line `as referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115TA, then, he or it shall be deemed to be an assessee in`
  line `default in respect of the amount of tax payable by him or it and all the provisions of this Act for the`
  line `collection and recovery of income-tax shall apply.`
  line `4 [ 115TCA. Tax on income from securitisation trusts. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `this Act, any income accruing or arising to, or received by, a person, being an investor of a securitisation`
  line `trust, out of investments made in the securitisation trust, shall be chargeable to income-tax in the same`
  line `manner as if it were the income accruing or arising to, or received by, such person, had the investments`
  line `by the securitisation trust been made directly by him.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
  line `2. Sub-section ( 3 ) omitted by Act 25 of 2014, s. 43 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 59 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 61, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_504_footnotes:
