  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_505_footnotes
  sourcePage 505
obj_root_law_sections_505_content:
  string
  line 505
  line `( 2 ) The income paid or credited by the securitisation trust shall be deemed to be of the same nature`
  line `and in the same proportion in the hands of the person referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), as if it had been`
  line `received by, or had accrued or arisen to, the securitisation trust during the previous year.`
  line `( 3 ) The income accruing or arising to, or received by, the securitisation trust, during a previous year,`
  line `if not paid or credited to the person referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), shall be deemed to have been credited to`
  line `the account of the said person on the last day of the previous year in the same proportion in which such`
  line `person would have been entitled to receive the income had it been paid in the previous year.`
  line `( 4 ) The person responsible for crediting or making payment of the income on behalf of securitisation`
  line `trust and the securitisation trust shall furnish, within such period, as may be prescribed, to the person who`
  line `is liable to tax in respect of such income and to the prescribed income-tax authority, a statement in such`
  line `form and verified in such manner, giving details of the nature of the income paid or credited during the`
  line `previous year and such other relevant details, as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 5 ) Any income which has been included in the total income of the person referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ), in a previous year, on account of it having accrued or arisen in the said previous year,`
  line `shall not be included in the total income of such person in the previous year in which such income is`
  line `actually paid to him by the securitisation trust.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this Chapter, —`
  line `( a ) “investor” means a person who is holder of any securitised debt instrument or securities 1 [or`
  line `security receipt] issued by the securitisation trust;`
  line `( b ) “securities” means debt securities issued by a Special Purpose Vehicle as referred to in the`
  line `guidelines on securitisation of standard assets issued by the Reserve Bank of India;`
  line `( c ) “securitised debt instrument” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause ( s ) of`
  line `sub-regulation (1) of regulation 2 of the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Public Offer and`
  line `Listing of Securitised Debt Instruments) Regulations, 2008 made under the Securities and Exchange`
  line `Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992) and the Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956`
  line `(42 of 1956);`
  line `( d ) “securitisation trust” means a trust, being a —`
  line `( i ) “special purpose distinct entity” as defined in clause ( u ) of sub-regulation (1) of`
  line `regulation 2 of the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Public Offer and Listing of`
  line `Securitised Debt Instruments) Regulations, 2008 made under the Securities and Exchange Board`
  line `of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992) and the Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956),`
  line `and regulated under the said regulations; or`
  line `( ii ) “Special Purpose Vehicle” as defined in, and regulated by, the guidel ines on`
  line `securitisation of standard assets issued by the Reserve Bank of India; 1 [or]`
  line `1 [( iii ) trust set-up by a securitisation company or a reconstruction company formed, for the`
  line `purposes of the Securitisation and Reconstruction of Financial Assets and Enforcement of`
  line `Security Interest Act, 2002 (54 of 2002), or in pursuance of any guidelines or directions issued`
  line `for the said purposes by the Reserve Bank of India,]`
  line `which fulfils such conditions, as may be prescribed.]`
  line `1 [( e ) “security receipt” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause ( zg ) of sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) of section 2 of the Securitisation and Reconstruction of Financial Assets and Enforcement of`
  line `Security Interest Act, 2002 (54 of 2002).]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 60 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
