  sourcePage 506
obj_root_law_sections_506_content:
  string
  line 506
  line `1 [ CHAPTER XIIEB`
  line `S PECIAL PROVISIONS RELATING TO TAX ON ACCRETED INCOME OF CERTAIN TRUSTS AND`
  line INSTITUTIONS
  line `115TD.Tax on accreted income. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, where in any`
  line `previous year, a trust or institution registered under section 12AA has —`
  line `( a ) converted into any form which is not eligible for grant of registration under section 12AA;`
  line `( b ) merged with any entity other than an entity which is a trust or institution having objects`
  line `similar to it and registered under section 12AA; or`
  line `( c ) failed to transfer upon dissolution all its assets to any other trust or institution registered`
  line `under section 12AA or to any fund or institution or trust or any university or other educational`
  line `institution or any hospital or other medical institution referred to in sub-clause ( iv ) or sub-clause ( v )`
  line `or sub-clause ( vi ) or sub-clause ( via ) of clause ( 23C ) of section 10, within a period of twelve months`
  line `from the end of the month in which the dissolution takes place,`
  line `then, in addition to the income-tax chargeable in respect of the total income of such trust or institution,`
  line `the accreted income of the trust or the institution as on the specified date shall be charged to tax and such`
  line `trust or institution, as the case may be, shall be liable to pay additional income-tax (herein referred to as`
  line `tax on accreted income) at the maximum marginal rate on the accreted income.`
  line `( 2 ) The accreted income for the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ) means the amount by which the aggregate`
  line `fair market value of the total assets of the trust or the institution, as on the specified date, exceeds the total`
  line `liability of such trust or institution computed in accordance with the method of valuation as may be`
  line `prescribed:`
  line `Provided that so much of the accreted income as is attributable to the following asset and liability, if`
  line `any, related to such asset shall be ignored for the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), namely: —`
  line `( i ) any asset which is established to have been directly acquired by the trust or institution out of`
  line `its income of the nature referred to in clause ( 1 ) of section 10;`
  line `( ii ) any asset acquired by the trust or institution during the period beginning from the date of its`
  line `creation or establishment and ending on the date from which the registration under section`
  line `12AA became effective, if the trust or institution has not been allowed any benefit of section`
  line `11 and 12 during the said period:`
  line `Provided further that where due to the first proviso to sub-section ( 2 ) of section 12A, the benefit`
  line `of section 11 and 12 have been allowed to the trust or the institution in respect of any previous year or`
  line `years beginning prior to the date from which the registration under section 12AA is effective, then, for the`
  line `purposes of clause ( ii ) of the first proviso, the registration shall be deemed to have become effective from`
  line `the first day of the earliest previous year:`
  line `Provided also that while computing the accreted income in respect of a case referred to in clause ( c )`
  line `of sub-section ( 1 ), assets and liabilities, if any, related to such asset, which have been transferred to any`
  line `other trust or institution registered under section 12AA or to any fund or institution or trust or any`
  line `university or other educational institution or any hospital or other medical institution referred to in sub-`
  line `clause ( iv ) or sub-clause ( v ) or sub-clause ( vi ) or sub-clause ( via ) of clause ( 23C ) of section 10, within the`
  line `period specified in the said clause, shall be ignored.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 62 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_506_footnotes:
