  title `Page 507`
  content obj_root_law_sections_507_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_507_footnotes
  sourcePage 507
obj_root_law_sections_507_content:
  string
  line 507
  line `( 3 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), a trust or an institution shall be deemed to have been`
  line `converted into any form not eligible for registration under section 12AA in a previous year, if, —`
  line `( i ) the registration granted to it under section 12AA has been cancelled; or`
  line `( ii ) it has adopted or undertaken modification of its objects which do not conform to the`
  line `conditions of registration and it, —`
  line `( a ) has not applied for fresh registration under section 12AA in the said previous year; or`
  line `( b ) has filed application for fresh registration under section 12AA but the said application has`
  line `been rejected.`
  line `( 4 ) Notwithstanding that no income-tax is payable by a trust or the institution on its total income`
  line `computed in accordance with the provisions of this Act, the tax on the accreted income under sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) shall be payable by such trust or the institution.`
  line `( 5 ) The principal officer or the trustee of the trust or the institution, as the case may be, and the trust`
  line `or the institution shall also be liable to pay the tax on accreted income to the credit of the Central`
  line `Government within fourteen days from, —`
  line `( i ) the date on which, —`
  line `( a ) the period for filing appeal under section 253 against the order cancelling the registration`
  line `expires and no appeal has been filed by the trust or the institution; or`
  line `( b ) the order in any appeal, confirming the cancellation of the registration, is received by the`
  line `trust or institution,`
  line `in a case referred to in clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 3 );`
  line `( ii ) the end of the previous year in a case referred to in sub-clause ( a ) of clause ( ii ) of sub-section`
  line `( 3 );`
  line `( iii ) the date on which, —`
  line `( a ) the period for filing appeal under section 253 against the order rejecting the application`
  line `expires and no appeal has been filed by the trust or the institution; or`
  line `( b ) the order in any appeal, confirming the cancellation of the application, is received by the`
  line `trust or institution,`
  line `in a case referred to in sub-clause ( b ) of clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 3 );`
  line `( iv ) the date of merger in a case referred to in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 );`
  line `( v ) the date on which the period of twelve months referred to in clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 1 )`
  line expires.
  line `( 6 ) The tax on the accreted income by the trust or the institution shall be treated as the final payment`
  line `of tax in respect of the said income and no further credit therefor shall be claimed by the trust or the`
  line `institution or by any other person in respect of the amount of tax so paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_507_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_508:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-508
  sectionNo (508)
  orderNo 508
  title `Page 508`
  content obj_root_law_sections_508_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_508_footnotes
  sourcePage 508
obj_root_law_sections_508_content:
  string
  line 508
  line `( 7 ) No deduction under any other provision of this Act shall be allowed to the trust or the institution`
  line `or any other person in respect of the income which has been charged to tax under sub-section ( 1 ) or the`
  line `tax thereon.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “date of conversion” means,—`
  line `( a ) the date of the order cancelling the registration under section 12AA, in a case referred to`
  line `in clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 3 ); or`
  line `( b ) the date of adoption or modification of any object, in a case referred to in clause ( ii ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 3 );`
  line `( ii ) “specified date” means,—`
  line `( a ) the date of conversion in a case falling under clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 );`
  line `( b ) the date of merger in a case falling under clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ); and`
  line `( c ) the date of dissolution in a case falling under clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 1 );`
  line `( iii ) registration under section 12AA shall include any registration obtained under section 12A as`
  line `it stood before its amendment by the Finance (No. 2) Act, 1996 (33 of 1996).`
  line `115TE. Interest payable for non-payment of tax by trust or institution. — Where the principal`
  line `officer or the trustee of the trust or the institution and the trust or the institution fails to pay the whole or`
  line `any part of the tax on the accreted income referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115TD, within the time`
  line `allowed under sub-section ( 5 ) of that section, he or it shall be liable to pay simple interest at the rate of`
  line `one per cent for every month or part thereof on the amount of such tax for the period beginning on the`
  line `date immediately after the last date on which such tax was payable and ending with the date on which the`
  line `tax is actually paid.`
  line `115TF.When trust or institution is deemed to be assessee in default. — ( 1 ) If any principal officer`
  line `or the trustee of the trust or the institution and the trust or the institution does not pay tax on accreted`
  line `income in accordance with the provisions of section 115TD, then, he or it shall be deemed to be an`
  line `assessee in default in respect of the amount of tax payable by him or it and all the provisions of this Act`
  line `for the collection and recovery of income-tax shall apply.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), in a case where the tax on accreted income`
  line `is payable under the circumstances referred to in clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115TD, the`
  line `person to whom any asset forming part of the computation of accreted income under sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `thereof has been transferred, shall be deemed to be an assessee in default in respect of such tax and`
  line `interest thereon and all the provisions of this Act for the collection and recovery of income-tax shall`
  line `apply:`
  line `Provided that the liability of the person referred to in this sub-section shall be limited to the extent to`
  line `which the asset received by him is capable of meeting the liability.]`
obj_root_law_sections_508_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_509:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-509
