obj_root_law_sections_510_content:
  string
  line 510
  line `1 [ CHAPTER XIIFA`
  line `S PECIAL PROVISIONS RELATING TO BUSINESS TRUSTS`
  line `115UA. Tax on income of unit holder and business trust. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other provisions of this Act, any income distributed by a business trust to its unit holders`
  line `shall be deemed to be of the same nature and in the same proportion in the hands of the unit holder as it`
  line `had been received by, or accrued to, the business trust.`
  line `( 2 ) Subject to the provisions of section 111A and section 112, the total income of a business trust`
  line `shall be charged to tax at the maximum marginal rate.`
  line `( 3 ) If in any previous year, the distributed income or any part thereof, received by a unit holder from`
  line `the business trust is of the nature as referred to 2 [in sub-clause ( a ) of clause ( 23FC )] 3 [or clause ( 23FCA )]`
  line `of section 10, then, such distributed income or part thereof shall be deemed to be income of such unit`
  line `holder and shall be charged to tax as income of the previous year.`
  line `( 4 ) Any person responsible for making payment of the income distributed on behalf of a business`
  line `trust to a unit holder shall furnish a statement to the unit holder and the prescribed authority, within such`
  line `time and in such form and manner as may be prescribed, giving the details of the nature of the income`
  line `paid during the previous year and such other details as may be prescribed.]`
  line `4 [CHAPTER XIIFB`
  line `S PECIAL PROVISIONS RELATING TO TAX ON INCOME OF INVESTMENT FUNDS AND INCOME RECEIVED FROM`
  line `SUCH FUNDS`
  line `115UB. Tax on income of investment fund and its unit holders. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other provisions of this Act and subject to the provisions of this Chapter, any income`
  line `accruing or arising to, or received by, a person, being a unit holder of an investment fund, out of`
  line `investments made in the investment fund, shall be chargeable to income-tax in the same manner as if it`
  line `were the income accruing or arising to, or received by, such person had the investments made by the`
  line `investment fund been made directly by him.`
  line `( 2 ) Where in any previous year, the net result of computation of total income of the investment fund`
  line `[without giving effect to the provisions of clause ( 23FBA ) of section 10] is a loss under any head of`
  line `income and such loss cannot be or is not wholly set-off against income under any other head of income of`
  line `the said previous year, then, —`
  line `( i ) such loss shall be allowed to be carried forward and it shall be set-off by the investment fund`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of Chapter VI; and`
  line `( ii ) such loss shall be ignored for the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 3 ) The income paid or credited by the investment fund shall be deemed to be of the same nature and`
  line `in the same proportion in the hands of the person referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), as if it had been received`
  line `by, or had accrued or arisen to, the investment fund during the previous year subject to the provisions of`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ).`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 44 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 63, for “in clause (23FC)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 33, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_510_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_511:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-511
