  content obj_root_law_sections_511_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_511_footnotes
  sourcePage 511
obj_root_law_sections_511_content:
  string
  line 511
  line `( 4 ) The total income of the investment fund shall be charged to tax —`
  line `( i ) at the rate or rates as specified in the Finance Act of the relevant year, where such fund is a`
  line `company or a firm; or`
  line `( ii ) at maximum marginal rate in any other case.`
  line `( 5 ) The provisions of Chapter XIID or Chapter XIIE shall not apply to the income paid by an`
  line `investment fund under this Chapter.`
  line `( 6 ) The income accruing or arising to, or received by, the investment fund, during a previous year, if`
  line `not paid or credited to the person referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), shall subject to the provisions of sub-`
  line `section ( 2 ), be deemed to have been credited to the account of the said person on the last day of the`
  line `previous year in the same proportion in which such person would have been entitled to receive the income`
  line `had it been paid in the previous year.`
  line `( 7 ) The person responsible for crediting or making payment of the income on behalf of an investment`
  line `fund and the investment fund shall furnish, within such time as may be prescribed 2, to the person who is`
  line `liable to tax in respect of such income and to the prescribed income-tax authority, a statement in the`
  line `prescribed form and verified in such manner, giving details of the nature of the income paid or credited`
  line `during the previous year and such other relevant details, as may be prescribed.`
  line `Explanation 1. — For the purposes of this Chapter, —`
  line `( a ) “investment fund” means any fund established or incorporated in India in the form of a trust`
  line `or a company or a limited liability partnership or a body corporate which has been granted a`
  line `certificate of registration as a Category I or a Category II Alternative Investment Fund and is`
  line `regulated under the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Alternative Investment Fund)`
  line `Regulations, 2012, made under the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992);`
  line `( b ) “trust” means a trust established under the Indian Trusts Act, 1882 (2 of 1882) or under any`
  line `other law for the time being in force;`
  line `( c ) “unit” means beneficial interest of an investor in the investment fund or a scheme of the`
  line `investment fund and shall include shares or partnership interests.`
  line `Explanation 2. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that any income which has been`
  line `included in total income of the person referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) in a previous year, on account of it`
  line `having accrued or arisen in the said previous year, shall not be included in the total income of such person`
  line `in the previous year in which such income is actually paid to him by the investment fund.]`
  line `1 [CHAPTER XIIG`
  line `S PECIAL PROVISIONS RELATING TO INCOME OF SHIPPING COMPANIES`
  line `A. — Meaning of certain expressions`
  line `115V. Definitions. — In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “bareboat charter” means hiring of a ship for a stipulated period on terms which give the`
  line `charterer possession and control of the ship, including the right to appoint the master and crew;`
  line `( b ) “bareboat charter - cum - demise” means a bareboat charter where the ownership of the ship is`
  line `intended to be transferred after a specified period to the company to whom it has been chartered;`
  line `( c ) “Director - General of Shipping” means the Director -General of Shipping appointed`
  line `by the Central Government under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 7 of the Merchant Shipping`
  line `Act, 1958 (44 of 1958);`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_511_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_512:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-512
  sectionNo (512)
  orderNo 512
  title `Page 512`
  content obj_root_law_sections_512_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_512_footnotes
  sourcePage 512
obj_root_law_sections_512_content:
  string
  line 512
  line `( d ) “ factory ship ” includes a vessel providing processing services in respect of processing of the`
  line `fishing produce;`
  line `( e ) “fishing vessel” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( 12 ) of section 3 of the`
  line `Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958);`
  line `( f ) “pleasure craft” means a ship of a kind whose primary use is for the purposes of sport or`
  line recreation;
  line `( g ) “qualifying company” mea ns a company referred to in section 115VC;`
  line `( h ) “qualifying ship” means a ship referred to in section 115VD;`
  line `( i ) “seagoing ship” means a ship if it is certified as such by the competent authority of any`
  line country;
  line `( j ) “tonnage income” means the income of a tonnage tax company computed in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of this Chapter;`
  line `( k ) “tonnage tax activities” means the activities referred to in sub -sections ( 2 ) and ( 5 ) of section`
  line 115V-I;
  line `( l ) “tonnage tax company” means a qualifying company in relation to which tonnage tax option`
  line `is in force;`
  line `( m ) “tonnage tax scheme” means a scheme for computation of profits and gains of business of`
  line `operating qualifying ships under the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line `B. — Computation of tonnage income from business of operating qualifying ships`
  line `115VA. Computation of profits and gains from the business of operating qualifying ships. —`
  line `Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in sections 28 to 43C, in the case of a company, the`
  line `income from the business of operating qualifying ships, may, at its option, be computed in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of this Chapter and such income shall be deemed to be the profits and gains of such`
  line `business chargeable to tax under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession”.`
  line `115VB. Operating ships. — For the purposes of this Chapter, a company shall be regarded as`
  line `operating a ship if it operates any ship whether owned or chartered by it and includes a case where even a`
  line `part of the ship has been chartered in by it in an arrangement such as slot charter, space charter or joint`
  line `charter:`
  line `Provided that a company shall not be regarded as the operator of a ship which has been chartered out`
  line `by it on bareboat charter- cum -demise terms or on bareboat charter terms for a period exceeding three`
  line years.
  line `115VC. Qualifying company. — For the purposes of this Chapter, a company is a qualifying`
  line `company if —`
  line `( a ) it is an Indian company;`
  line `( b ) the place of effective management of the company is in India;`
  line `( c ) it owns at least one qualifying ship; and`
  line `( d ) the main object of the company is to carry on the business of operating ships.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, “place of effective management of the company”`
  line `means —`
  line `( A ) the place where the board of directors of the company or its executive directors, as the case`
  line `may be, make their decisions; or`
obj_root_law_sections_512_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_513:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-513
  sectionNo (513)
  orderNo 513
  title `Page 513`
  content obj_root_law_sections_513_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_513_footnotes
  sourcePage 513
obj_root_law_sections_513_content:
  string
  line 513
  line `( B ) in a case where the board of directors routinely approve the commercial and strategic`
  line `decisions made by the executive directors or officers of the company, the place where such executive`
  line `directors or officers of the company perform their functions.`
  line `115VD. Qualifying ship. — For the purposes of this Chapter, a ship is a qualifying ship if —`
  line `( a ) it is a sea going ship or vessel of fifteen net tonnage or more;`
  line `( b ) it is a ship registered under the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958), or a ship`
  line `registered outside India in respect of which a licence has been issued by the Director-General of`
  line `Shipping under section 406 or section 407 of the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958); and`
  line `( c ) a valid certificate in respect of such ship indicating its net tonnage is in force,`
  line `but does not include —`
  line `( i ) a sea going ship or vessel if the main purpose for which it is used is the provision of`
  line `goods or services of a kind normally provided on land;`
  line `( ii ) fishing vessels;`
  line `( iii ) factory ships;`
  line `( iv ) pleasure crafts;`
  line `( v ) harbour and river ferries;`
  line `( vi ) offshore installations;`
  line `1 * * * *`
  line `( viii ) a qualifying ship which is used as a fishing vessel for a period of more than thirty days`
  line `during a previous year.`
  line `115VE. Manner of computation of income under tonnage tax scheme. — ( 1 ) A tonnage tax`
  line `company engaged in the business of operating qualifying ships shall compute the profits from such`
  line `business under the tonnage tax scheme.`
  line `( 2 ) The business of operating qualifying ships giving rise to income referred to in sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 115V-I shall be considered as a separate business (hereafter in this Chapter referred to as the`
  line `tonnage tax business) distinct from all other activities or business carried on by the company.`
  line `( 3 ) The profits referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be computed separately from the profits and gains`
  line `from any other business.`
  line `( 4 ) The tonnage tax scheme shall apply only if an option to that effect is made in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of section 115VP.`
  line `( 5 ) Where a company engaged in the business of operating qualifying ships is not covered under the`
  line `tonnage tax scheme or, has not made an option to that effect, as the case may be, the profits and gains of`
  line `such company from such business shall be computed in accordance with the other provisions of this Act.`
  line `115VF. Tonnage income. — Subject to the other provisions of this Chapter, the tonnage income shall`
  line `be computed in accordance with section 115VG and the income so computed shall be deemed to be the`
  line `profits chargeable under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession” and the relevant shipping`
  line `income referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115V-I shall not be chargeable to tax.`
  line `1. Clause ( vii ) omitted by Act 18 of 2005, s. 36 (w.e.f 1-4-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_513_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_514:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-514
  sectionNo (514)
  orderNo 514
  title `Page 514`
  content obj_root_law_sections_514_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_514_footnotes
  sourcePage 514
obj_root_law_sections_514_content:
  string
  line 514
  line `115VG. Computation of tonnage income. — ( 1 ) The tonnage income of a tonnage tax company for a`
  line `previous year shall be the aggregate of the tonnage income of each qualifying ship computed in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of sub-sections ( 2 ) and ( 3 ).`
  line `( 2 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), the tonnage income of each qualifying ship shall be the daily`
  line `tonnage income of each such ship multiplied by —`
  line `( a ) the number of days in the previous year; or`
  line `( b ) the number of days in part of the previous year in case the ship is operated by the company as`
  line `a qualifying ship for only part of the previous year, as the case may be.`
  line `( 3 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 2 ), the daily tonnage income of a qualifying ship having tonnage`
  line `referred to in column (1) of the Table below shall be the amount specified in the corresponding entry in`
  line `column (2) of the Table:`
  line `1 [TABLE`
  line `Qualifying ship having net to nnage Amount of daily tonnage income`
  line `(1) (2)`
  line `up to 1,000 Rs. 70 for each 100 tons`
  line `exceeding 1,000 but not more than 10,000 Rs. 700 plus Rs. 53 for each 100 tons exceeding`
  line `1,000 tons`
  line `exceeding 10,000 but not more than 25,000 Rs. 5,470 plus Rs. 42 for each 100 tons exceeding`
  line `10,000 tons`
  line `exceeding 25,000 Rs. 11,770 plus Rs. 29 for each 100 tons exceeding`
  line `25,000 tons.]`
  line `( 4 ) For the purposes of this Chapter, the tonnage shall mean the tonnage of a ship indicated in the`
  line `certificate referred to in section 115VX and includes the deemed tonnage computed in the prescribed`
  line manner.
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- section, “deemed tonnage” shall be the tonnage in respect`
  line `of an arrangement of purchase of slots, slot charter and an arrangement of sharing of break-bulk vessel.`
  line `( 5 ) The tonnage shall be rounded off to the nearest multiple of hundred tons and for this purpose any`
  line `tonnage consisting of kilograms shall be ignored and thereafter if such tonnage is not a multiple of`
  line `hundred, then, if the last figure in that amount is fifty tons or more, the tonnage shall be increased to the`
  line `next higher tonnage which is a multiple of hundred and if the last figure is less than fifty tons, the tonnage`
  line `shall be reduced to the next lower tonnage which is a multiple of hundred; and the tonnage so rounded off`
  line `shall be the tonnage of the ship for the purposes of this section.`
  line `( 6 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, no deduction or set off`
  line `shall be allowed in computing the tonnage income under this Chapter.`
  line `115VH. Calculation in case of joint operation, etc. — ( 1 ) Where a qualifying ship is operated by two`
  line `or more companies by way of joint interest in the ship or by way of an agreement for the use of the ship`
  line `and their respective shares are definite and ascertainable, the tonnage income of each such company shall`
  line `be an amount equal to a share of income proportionate to its share of that interest.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 58, for the Table (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_514_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_515:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-515
  sectionNo (515)
  orderNo 515
  title `Page 515`
  content obj_root_law_sections_515_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_515_footnotes
  sourcePage 515
obj_root_law_sections_515_content:
  string
  line 515
  line `( 2 ) Subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ), where two or more companies are operators of a`
  line `qualifying ship, the tonnage income of each company shall be computed as if each had been the only`
  line operator.
  line `115VI. Relevant shipping income. — ( 1 ) For the purposes of this Chapter, the relevant shipping`
  line `income of a tonnage tax company means —`
  line `( i ) its profits from core activities referred to in sub-section ( 2 );`
  line `( ii ) its profits from incidental activities referred to in sub-section ( 5 ):`
  line `Provided that where the aggregate of all such incomes specified in clause ( ii ) exceeds`
  line `one-fourth per cent of the turnover from core activities referred to in sub-section ( 2 ), such excess shall not`
  line `form part of the relevant shipping income for the purposes of this Chapter and shall be taxable under the`
  line `other provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) The core activities of a tonnage tax company shall be —`
  line `( i ) its activities from operating qualifying ships; and`
  line `( ii ) other ship-related activities mentioned as under: —`
  line `( A ) shipping contracts in respect of —`
  line `( i ) earning from pooling arrangements;`
  line `( ii ) contracts of affreightment.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-clause, —`
  line `( a ) “pooling arrangement” means an agreement between two or more persons for providing`
  line `services through a pool or operating one or more ships and sharing earnings or operating profits`
  line `on the basis of mutually agreed terms;`
  line `( b ) “contract of affreightment” means a service contract under which a tonnage tax company`
  line `agrees to transport a specified quantity of specified products at a specified rate, between`
  line `designated loading and discharging ports over a specified period;`
  line `( B ) specific shipping trades, being —`
  line `( i ) on-board or on-shore activities of passenger ships comprising of fares and food and`
  line `beverages consumed on board;`
  line `( ii ) slot charters, space charters, joint charters, feeder services, container box leasing of`
  line `container shipping.`
  line `( 3 ) The Central Government, if it considers necessary or expedient so to do, may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, exclude any activity referred to in clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 2 ) or prescribe the limit`
  line `up to which such activities shall be included in the core activities for the purposes of this section.`
  line `( 4 ) Every notification issued under this Chapter shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is issued,`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the notification, or both Houses agree that the notification should not be issued, the`
  line `notification shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be;`
  line `so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_515_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_516:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-516
  sectionNo (516)
  orderNo 516
  title `Page 516`
  content obj_root_law_sections_516_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_516_footnotes
  sourcePage 516
obj_root_law_sections_516_content:
  string
  line 516
  line `( 5 ) The incidental activities shall be the activities which are incidental to the core activities and which`
  line `may be prescribed for the purpose.`
  line `( 6 ) Where a tonnage tax company operates any ship, which is not a qualifying ship, the income`
  line `attributable to operating such non-qualifying ship shall be computed in accordance with the other`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 7 ) Where any goods or services held for the purposes of tonnage tax business are transferred to any`
  line `other business carried on by a tonnage tax company, or where any goods or services held for the purposes`
  line `of any other business carried on by such tonnage tax company are transferred to the tonnage tax business`
  line `and, in either case, the consideration, if any, for such transfer as recorded in the accounts of the tonnage`
  line `tax business does not correspond to the market value of such goods or services as on the date of the`
  line `transfer, then, the relevant shipping income under this section shall be computed as if the transfer, in`
  line `either case, had been made at the market value of such goods or services as on that date:`
  line `Provided that where, in the opinion of the Assessing Officer, the computation of the relevant shipping`
  line `income in the manner hereinbefore specified presents exceptional difficulties, the Assessing Officer may`
  line `compute such income on such reasonable basis as he may deem fit.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- section, “market value”, in relation to any goods or`
  line `services, means the price that such goods or services would ordinarily fetch on sale in the open market.`
  line `( 8 ) Where it appears to the Assessing Officer that, owing to the close connection between the tonnage`
  line `tax company and any other person, or for any other reason, the course of business between them is so`
  line `arranged that the business transacted between them produces to the tonnage tax company more than the`
  line `ordinary profits which might be expected to arise in the tonnage tax business, the Assessing Officer shall,`
  line `in computing the relevant shipping income of the tonnage tax company for the purposes of this Chapter,`
  line `take the amount of income as may reasonably be deemed to have been derived therefrom.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this Chapter, in case the relevant shipping income of a tonnage tax`
  line `company is a loss, then, such loss shall be ignored for the purposes of computing tonnage income.`
  line `115VJ. Treatment of common costs. — ( 1 ) Where a tonnage tax company also carries on any`
  line `business or activity other than the tonnage tax business, common costs attributable to the tonnage tax`
  line `business shall be determined on a reasonable basis.`
  line `( 2 ) Where any asset, other than a qualifying ship, is not exclusively used for the tonnage tax business`
  line `by the tonnage tax company, depreciation on such asset shall be allocated between its tonnage tax`
  line `business and other business on a fair proportion to be determined by the Assessing Officer, having regard`
  line `to the use of such asset for the purpose of the tonnage tax business and for the other business.`
  line `115VK. Depreciation. — ( 1 ) For the purposes of computing depreciation under clause ( iv ) of`
  line `section 115VL, the depreciation for the first previous year of the tonnage tax scheme (hereafter in this`
  line `section referred to as the first previous year) shall be computed on the written down value of the`
  line `qualifying ships as specified under sub-section ( 2 ).`
  line `( 2 ) The written down value of the block of assets, being ships, as on the first day of the first previous`
  line `year, shall be divided in the ratio of the book written down value of the qualifying ships (hereafter in this`
  line `section referred to as the qualifying assets) and the book written down value of the non-qualifying ships`
  line `(hereafter in this section referred to as the other assets).`
  line `( 3 ) The block of qualifying assets as determined under sub-section ( 2 ) shall constitute a separate`
  line `block of assets for the purposes of this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_516_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_517:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-517
  sectionNo (517)
  orderNo 517
  title `Page 517`
  content obj_root_law_sections_517_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_517_footnotes
  sourcePage 517
obj_root_law_sections_517_content:
  string
  line 517
  line `( 4 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 2 ), the book written down value of the block of qualifying assets`
  line `and the block of other assets shall be computed in the following manner, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the book written down value of each qualifying asset and each other asset as on the first day`
  line `of the previous year and which form part of the block of assets to be divided shall be determined by`
  line `taking the book written down value of each asset appearing in the books of account as on the last day`
  line `of the preceding previous year:`
  line `Provided that any change in the value of the assets consequent to their revaluation after the date`
  line `on which the Finance (No. 2) Act, 2004 receives the assent of the President shall be ignored;`
  line `( b ) the book written down value of all the qualifying assets and other assets shall be aggregated;`
  line and
  line `( c ) the ratio of the aggregate book written down value of the qualifying assets to the aggregate`
  line `book written down value of the other assets shall be determined.`
  line `( 5 ) Where an asset forming part of a block of qualifying assets begins to be used for purposes other`
  line `than the tonnage tax business, an appropriate portion of the written down value allocable to such asset`
  line `shall be reduced from the written down value of that block and shall be added to the block of other assets.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, appropriate portion of the written down value`
  line `allocable to the asset, which begins to be used for purposes other than the tonnage tax business, shall be`
  line `an amount which bears the same proportion to the written down value of the block of qualifying assets as`
  line `on the first day of the previous year as the book written down value of the asset beginning to be used for`
  line `purposes other than tonnage tax business bears to the book written down value of all the assets forming`
  line `the block of qualifying asset.`
  line `( 6 ) Where an asset forming part of a block of other assets begins to be used for tonnage tax business,`
  line `an appropriate portion of the written down value allocable to such asset shall be reduced from the written`
  line `down value of the block of other assets and shall be added to the block of qualifying asset.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, appropriate portion of written down value`
  line `allocable to the asset which begins to be used for the tonnage tax business shall be an amount which bears`
  line `the same proportion to the written down value of the block of other assets as on the first day of the`
  line `previous year as the book written down value of the asset beginning to be used for tonnage tax business`
  line `bears to the total book written down value of all the assets forming the block of other assets.`
  line `( 7 ) For the purposes of computing depreciation under clause ( iv ) of section 115VL in respect of an`
  line `asset mentioned in sub-sections ( 5 ) and ( 6 ), depreciation computed for the previous year shall be`
  line `allocated in the ratio of the number of days for which the asset was used for the tonnage tax business and`
  line `for purposes other than tonnage tax business.`
  line `Explanation 1. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that for the purposes of this Act,`
  line `depreciation on the block of qualifying assets and block of other assets so created shall be allowed as if`
  line `such written down value referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) had been brought forward from the preceding`
  line `previous year.`
  line `Explanation 2. —For the purposes of this section, “book written down value” means the written down`
  line `value as appearing in the books of account.`
obj_root_law_sections_517_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_518:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-518
  sectionNo (518)
  orderNo 518
  title `Page 518`
  content obj_root_law_sections_518_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_518_footnotes
  sourcePage 518
obj_root_law_sections_518_content:
  string
  line 518
  line `115VL. General exclusion of deduction and set off, etc. — Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `any other provision of this Act, in computing the tonnage income of a tonnage tax company for any`
  line `previous year (hereafter in this section referred to as the “relevant previous year”) in which it is`
  line `chargeable to tax in accordance with this Chapter —`
  line `( i ) sections 30 to 43B shall apply as if every loss, allowance or deduction referred to therein and`
  line `relating to or allowable for any of the relevant previous years, had been given full effect to for that`
  line `previous year itself;`
  line `( ii ) no loss referred to in sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 3 ) of section 70 or sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 71 or sub-section ( 1 ) of section 72 or sub-section ( 1 ) of section 72A, in so far as such loss`
  line `relates to the business of operating qualifying ships of the company, shall be carried forward or set off`
  line `where such loss relates to any of the previous years when the company is under the tonnage tax`
  line scheme;
  line `( iii ) no deduction shall be allowed under Chapter VIA in relation to the profits and gains from the`
  line `business of operating qualifying ships; and`
  line `( iv ) in computing the depreciation allowance under section 32, the written down value of any`
  line `asset used for the purposes of the tonnage tax business shall be computed as if the company has`
  line `claimed and has been actually allowed the deduction in respect of depreciation for the relevant`
  line `previous years.`
  line `115VM. Exclusion of loss. — ( 1 ) Section 72 shall apply in respect of any losses that have accrued to a`
  line `company before its option for tonnage tax scheme and which are attributable to its tonnage tax business,`
  line `as if such losses had been set off against the relevant shipping income in any of the previous years when`
  line `the company is under the tonnage tax scheme.`
  line `( 2 ) The losses referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall not be available for set off against any income other`
  line `than relevant shipping income in any previous year beginning on or after the company exercises its option`
  line `under section 115VP.`
  line `( 3 ) Any apportionment necessary to determine the losses referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be made`
  line `on a reasonable basis.`
  line `115VN. Chargeable gains from transfer of tonnage tax assets. — Any profits or gains arising from`
  line `the transfer of a capital asset being an asset forming part of the block of qualifying assets shall be`
  line `chargeable to income-tax in accordance with the provisions of section 45, read with section 50, and the`
  line `capital gains so arising shall be computed in accordance with the provisions of sections 45 to 51:`
  line `Provided that for the purpose of computing such profits or gains, the provisions of`
  line `section 50 shall have effect as if for the words “written down value of the block of assets”, the words`
  line `“written down value of the block of qualifying assets” had been substituted.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this Chapter, “written down value of the block of qualifying`
  line `assets” means the written down value computed in accordance with the provisions of sub -section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 115VK.`
  line `115V-O. Exclusion from provisions of section 115JB. — The book profit or loss derived from the`
  line `activities of a tonnage tax company, referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115V-I, shall be excluded`
  line `from the book profit of the company for the purposes of section 115JB.`
  line `C. — Procedure for option of tonnage tax scheme`
  line `115VP. Method and time of opting for tonnage tax scheme. — ( 1 ) A qualifying company may opt`
  line `for the tonnage tax scheme by making an application to the Joint Commissioner having jurisdiction over`
  line `the company in the form and manner as may be prescribed, for such scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_518_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_519:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-519
  sectionNo (519)
  orderNo 519
  title `Page 519`
  content obj_root_law_sections_519_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_519_footnotes
  sourcePage 519
obj_root_law_sections_519_content:
  string
  line 519
  line `( 2 ) The application under sub-section ( 1 ) may be made by any existing qualifying company at any`
  line `time after the 30th day of September, 2004 but before the 1st day of January, 2005 (hereafter referred to`
  line `as the “initial period”):`
  line `Provided that —`
  line `( i ) a company incorporated after the initial period; or`
  line `( ii ) a qualifying company incorporated before the initial period but which becomes a qualifying`
  line `company for the first time after the initial period,`
  line `may make an application within three months of the date of its incorporation or the date on which it`
  line `became a qualifying company, as the case may be.`
  line `( 3 ) On receipt of an application for option for tonnage tax scheme under sub-section ( 1 ), the Joint`
  line `Commissioner may call for such information or documents from the company as he thinks necessary in`
  line `order to satisfy himself about the eligibility of the company and after satisfying himself about such`
  line `eligibility of the company to make such option for tonnage tax scheme, he —`
  line `( i ) shall pass an order in writing approving the option for tonnage tax scheme; or`
  line `( ii ) shall, if he is not so satisfied, pass an order in writing refusing to approve the option for`
  line `tonnage tax scheme,`
  line `and a copy of such order shall be sent to the applicant:`
  line `Provided that no order under clause ( ii ) shall be passed unless the applicant has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line `( 4 ) Every order granting or refusing the approval of the option for tonnage tax scheme under`
  line `clause ( i ) or clause ( ii ), as the case may be, of sub-section ( 3 ) shall be passed before the expiry of one`
  line `month from the end of the month in which the application was received under sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 5 ) Where an order granting approval is passed under sub-section ( 3 ), the provisions of this Chapter`
  line `shall apply from the assessment year relevant to the previous year in which the option for tonnage tax`
  line `scheme is exercised.`
  line `115VQ. Period for which tonnage tax option to remain in force. — ( 1 ) An option for tonnage tax`
  line `scheme, after it has been approved under sub-section ( 3 ) of section 115VP, shall remain in force for a`
  line `period of ten years from the date on which such option has been exercised and shall be taken into account`
  line `from the assessment year relevant to the previous year in which such option is exercised.`
  line `( 2 ) An option for tonnage tax scheme shall cease to have effect from the assessment year relevant to`
  line `the previous year in which —`
  line `( a ) the qualifying company ceases to be a qualifying company;`
  line `( b ) a default is made in complying with the provisions contained in section 115VT or`
  line `section 115VU or section 115VV;`
  line `( c ) the tonnage tax company is excluded from the tonnage tax scheme under section 115VZC;`
  line `( d ) the qualifying company furnishes to the Assessing Officer, a declaration in writing to the`
  line `effect that the provisions of this Chapter may not be made applicable to it,`
  line `and the profits and gains of the company from the business of operating qualifying ships shall be`
  line `computed in accordance with the other provisions of this Act.`
  line `115VR. Renewal of tonnage tax scheme. — ( 1 ) An option for tonnage tax scheme approved under`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ) of section 115VP may be renewed within one year from the end of the previous year in`
  line `which the option ceases to have effect.`
  line `( 2 ) The provisions of sections 115VP and 115VQ shall apply in relation to a renewal of the option for`
  line `tonnage tax scheme in the same manner as they apply in relation to the approval of option for tonnage tax`
  line scheme.
obj_root_law_sections_519_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_520:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-520
  sectionNo (520)
  orderNo 520
  title `Page 520`
  content obj_root_law_sections_520_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_520_footnotes
  sourcePage 520
obj_root_law_sections_520_content:
  string
  line 520
  line `115VS. Prohibition to opt for tonnage tax scheme in certain cases. — A qualifying company,`
  line `which, on its own, opts out of the tonnage tax scheme or makes a default in complying with the`
  line `provisions of section 115VT or section 115VU or section 115VV or whose option has been excluded`
  line `from tonnage tax scheme in pursuance of an order made under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115VZC, shall`
  line `not be eligible to opt for tonnage tax scheme for a period of ten years from the date of opting out or`
  line `default or order, as the case may be.`
  line `D. — Conditions for applicability of tonnage tax scheme`
  line `115VT. Transfer of profits to Tonnage Tax Reserve Account. — ( 1 ) A tonnage tax company shall,`
  line `subject to and in accordance with the provisions of this section, be required to credit to a reserve account`
  line `(hereafter in this section referred to as the Tonnage Tax Reserve Account) an amount not less than twenty`
  line `per cent of the book profit derived from the activities referred to in clauses ( i ) and ( ii ) of sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 115V-I in each previous year to be utilised in the manner laid down in sub-section ( 3 ):`
  line `Provided that a tonnage tax company may transfer a sum in excess of twenty per cent of the book`
  line `profit and such excess sum transferred shall also be utilised in the manner laid down in sub-section ( 3 ).`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, “book profit” shall have the sa me meaning as in`
  line `the Explanation to sub-section ( 2 ) of section 115JB so far as it relates to the income derived from the`
  line `activities referred to in clauses ( i ) and ( ii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115V-I.`
  line `( 2 ) Where the company has book profit from the business of operating qualifying ships and book loss`
  line `from any other sources, and consequently, the company is not in a position to create the full or any part of`
  line `the reserves under sub-section ( 1 ), the company shall create the reserves to the extent possible in that`
  line `previous year and the shortfall, if any, shall be added to the amount of the reserves required to be created`
  line `for the following previous year and such shortfall shall be deemed to be part of the reserve requirement of`
  line `that following previous year:`
  line `Provided that to the extent the shortfall in creation of reserves during a particular previous year is`
  line `carried forward to the following previous year under this sub-section, the company shall be considered as`
  line `having created sufficient reserves for the first mentioned previous year:`
  line `Provided further that nothing contained in the first proviso shall apply in respect of the second year in`
  line `case the shortfall in creation of reserves continues for two consecutive previous years.`
  line `( 3 ) The amount credited to the Tonnage Tax Reserve Account under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be utilised`
  line `by the company before the expiry of a period of eight years next following the previous year in which the`
  line `amount was credited —`
  line `( a ) for acquiring a new ship for the purposes of the business of the company; and`
  line `( b ) until the acquisition of a new ship, for the purposes of the business of operating qualifying`
  line `ships other than for distribution by way of dividends or profits or for remittance outside India as`
  line `profits or for the creation of any asset outside India.`
  line `( 4 ) Where any amount credited to the Tonnage Tax Reserve Account under sub-section ( 1 ), —`
  line `( a ) has been utilised for any purpose other than that referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ); or`
  line `( b ) has not been utilised for the purpose specified in clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 3 ); or`
  line `( c ) has been utilised for the purpose of acquiring a new ship as specified in clause ( a ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ), but such ship is sold or otherwise transferred, other than in any scheme of demerger`
  line `by the company to any person at any time before the expiry of three years from the end of the`
  line `previous year in which it was acquired,`
  line `an amount which bears the same proportion to the total relevant shipping income of the year in which`
  line `such reserve was created, as the amount out of such reserve so utilised or not utilised bears to the total`
  line `reserve created during that year under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be taxable under the other provisions of this`
  line `Act —`
  line `( i ) in a case referred to in clause ( a ), in the year in which the amount was so utilised; or`
obj_root_law_sections_520_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_521:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-521
  sectionNo (521)
  orderNo 521
  title `Page 521`
  content obj_root_law_sections_521_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_521_footnotes
  sourcePage 521
obj_root_law_sections_521_content:
  string
  line 521
  line `( ii ) in a case referred to in clause ( b ), in the year immediately following the period of eight years`
  line `specified in sub-section ( 3 ); or`
  line `( iii ) in a case referred to in clause ( c ), in the year in which the sale or transfer took place:`
  line `Provided that the income so taxable under the other provisions of this Act shall be reduced by the`
  line `proportionate tonnage income charged to tax in the year of creation of such reserves.`
  line `( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Chapter, where the amount`
  line `credited to the Tonnage Tax Reserve Account in accordance with sub-section ( 1 ) is less than the`
  line `minimum amount required to be credited under sub-section ( 1 ), an amount which bears the same`
  line `proportion to the total relevant shipping income, as the shortfall in credit to the reserves bears to the`
  line `minimum reserve required to be credited under sub-section ( 1 ) shall not be taxable under the tonnage tax`
  line `scheme and shall be taxable under the other provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 6 ) If the reserve required to be created under sub-section ( 1 ) is not created for any two consecutive`
  line `previous years, the option of the company for tonnage tax scheme shall cease to have effect from the`
  line `beginning of the previous year following the second consecutive previous year in which the failure to`
  line `create the reserve under sub-section ( 1 ) had occurred.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, “new ship” includes a qualifying ship which, before`
  line `the date of acquisition by the qualifying company was used by any other person, if it was not at any time`
  line `previous to the date of such acquisition owned by any person resident in India.`
  line `115VU. Minimum training requirement for tonnage tax company. — ( 1 ) A tonnage tax company,`
  line `after its option has been approved under sub-section ( 3 ) of section 115VP, shall comply with the`
  line `minimum training requirement in respect of trainee officers in accordance with the guidelines framed by`
  line `the Director-General of Shipping and notified in the Official Gazette by the Central Government.`
  line `( 2 ) The tonnage tax company shall be required to furnish a copy of the certificate issued by the`
  line `Director-General of Shipping along with the return of income under section 139 to the effect that such`
  line `company has complied with the minimum training requirement in accordance with the guidelines referred`
  line `to in sub-section ( 1 ) for the previous year.`
  line `( 3 ) If the minimum training requirement is not complied with for any five consecutive previous years,`
  line `the option of the company for tonnage tax scheme shall cease to have effect from the beginning of the`
  line `previous year following the fifth consecutive previous year in which the failure to comply with the`
  line `minimum training requirement under sub-section ( 1 ) had occurred.`
  line `115VV. Limit for charter in of tonnage. — ( 1 ) In the case of every company which has opted for`
  line `tonnage tax scheme, not more than forty-nine per cent of the net tonnage of the qualifying ships operated`
  line `by it during any previous year shall be chartered in.`
  line `( 2 ) The proportion of net tonnage referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) in respect of a previous year shall be`
  line `calculated based on the average of net tonnage during that previous year.`
  line `( 3 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 2 ), the average of net tonnage shall be computed in such manner`
  line `as may be prescribed in consultation with the Director-General of Shipping.`
  line `( 4 ) Where the net tonnage of ships chartered in exceeds the limit under sub-section ( 1 ) during any`
  line `previous year, the total income of such company in relation to that previous year shall be computed as if`
  line `the option for tonnage tax scheme does not have effect for that previous year.`
  line `( 5 ) Where the limit under sub-section ( 1 ) had exceeded in any two consecutive previous years, the`
  line `option for tonnage tax scheme shall cease to have effect from the beginning of the previous year`
  line `following the second consecutive previous year in which the limit had exceeded.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, the term “chartered in” shall exclude a ship chartered`
  line `in by the company on bareboat charter- cum -demise terms.`
obj_root_law_sections_521_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_522:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-522
  sectionNo (522)
  orderNo 522
  title `Page 522`
  content obj_root_law_sections_522_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_522_footnotes
  sourcePage 522
obj_root_law_sections_522_content:
  string
  line 522
  line `115VW. Maintenance and audit of accounts. — An option for tonnage tax scheme by a tonnage tax`
  line `company shall not have effect in relation to a previous year unless such company —`
  line `( i ) maintains separate books of account in respect of the business of operating qualifying ships;`
  line and
  line `( ii ) furnishes, along with the return of income for that previous year, the report of an accountant,`
  line `in the prescribed form duly signed and verified by such accountant.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, “accountant” shall have the same meaning as in`
  line `the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288.`
  line `115VX. Determination of tonnage. — ( 1 ) For the purposes of this Chapter, —`
  line `( a ) the tonnage of a ship shall be determined in accordance with the valid certificate indicating`
  line `its tonnage;`
  line `( b ) “valid certificate” means,—`
  line `( i ) in case of ships registered in India —`
  line `( a ) having a length of less than twenty-four metres, a certificate issued under the`
  line `Merchant Shipping (Tonnage Measurement of Ship) Rules, 1987 made under the Merchant`
  line `Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958);`
  line `( b ) having a length of twenty-four metres or more, an international tonnage certificate`
  line `issued under the provisions of the Convention on Tonnage Measurement of Ships, 1969, as`
  line `specified in the Merchant Shipping (Tonnage Measurement of Ship) Rules, 1987 made under`
  line `the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958);`
  line `( ii ) in case of ships registered outside India, a licence issued by the Director-General of`
  line `Shipping under section 406 or section 407 of the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958)`
  line `specifying the net tonnage on the basis of Tonnage Certificate issued by the Flag State`
  line `Administration where the ship is registered or any other evidence acceptable to the Director-`
  line `General of Shipping produced by the ship owner while seeking permission for chartering in the`
  line ship.
  line `E. — Amalgamation and demerger of shipping companies`
  line `115VY. Amalgamation. — Where there has been an amalgamation of a company with another`
  line `company or companies, then, subject to the other provisions of this section, the provisions relating to the`
  line `tonnage tax scheme shall, as far as may be, apply to the amalgamated company if it is a qualifying`
  line `company:`
  line `Provided that where the amalgamated company is not a tonnage tax company, it shall exercise an`
  line `option for tonnage tax scheme under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115VP within three months from the date`
  line `of the approval of the scheme of amalgamation:`
  line `Provided further that where the amalgamating companies are tonnage tax companies, the provisions`
  line `of this Chapter shall, as far as may be, apply to the amalgamated company for such period as the option`
  line `for tonnage tax scheme which has the longest unexpired period continues to be in force:`
  line `Provided also that where one of the amalgamating companies is a qualifying company as on the 1st`
  line `day of October, 2004 and which has not exercised the option for tonnage tax scheme within the initial`
  line `period, the provisions of this Chapter shall not apply to the amalgamated company and the income of the`
  line `amalgamated company from the business of operating qualifying ships shall be computed in accordance`
  line `with the other provisions of this Act.`
  line `115VZ. Demerger. — Where in a scheme of demerger, the demerged company transfers its business`
  line `to the resulting company before the expiry of the option for tonnage tax scheme, then, subject to the other`
  line `provisions of this Chapter, the tonnage tax scheme shall, as far as may be, apply to the resulting company`
  line `for the unexpired period if it is a qualifying company:`
obj_root_law_sections_522_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_523:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-523
  sectionNo (523)
  orderNo 523
  title `Page 523`
  content obj_root_law_sections_523_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_523_footnotes
  sourcePage 523
obj_root_law_sections_523_content:
  string
  line 523
  line `Provided that the option for tonnage tax scheme in respect of the demerged company shall remain in`
  line `force for the unexpired period of the tonnage tax scheme if it continues to be a qualifying company.`
  line `F. — Miscellaneous`
  line `115VZA.Effect of temporarily ceasing to operate qualifying ships. — ( 1 ) A temporary cessation (as`
  line `against permanent cessation) of operating any qualifying ship by a company shall not be considered as a`
  line `cessation of operating of such qualifying ship and the company shall be deemed to be operating such`
  line `qualifying ship for the purposes of this Chapter.`
  line `( 2 ) Where a qualifying company continues to operate a ship, which temporarily ceases to be a`
  line `qualifying ship, such ship shall not be considered as a qualifying ship for the purposes of this Chapter.`
  line `G. — Provisions of this Chapter not to apply in certain cases`
  line `115VZB. Avoidance of tax. — ( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of this Chapter, the tonnage tax scheme`
  line `shall not apply where a tonnage tax company is a party to any transaction or arrangement which amounts`
  line `to an abuse of the tonnage tax scheme.`
  line `( 2 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), a transaction or arrangement shall be considered an abuse if`
  line `the entering into or the application of such transaction or arrangement results, or would but for this`
  line `section have resulted, in a tax advantage being obtained for —`
  line `( i ) a person other than a tonnage tax company; or`
  line `( ii ) a tonnage tax company in respect of its non-tonnage tax activities.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, “tax advantage” include,—`
  line `( i ) the determination of the allowance for any expense or interest, or the determination of any`
  line `cost or expense allocated or apportioned, or, as the case may be, which has the effect of reducing the`
  line `income or increasing the loss, as the case may be, from activities other than tonnage tax activities`
  line `chargeable to tax, computed on the basis of entries made in the books of account in respect of the`
  line `previous year in which the transaction was entered into; or`
  line `( ii ) a transaction or arrangement which produces to the tonnage tax company more than ordinary`
  line `profits which might be expected to arise from tonnage tax activities.`
  line `115VZC. Exclusion from tonnage tax scheme. — ( 1 ) Where a tonnage tax company is a party to any`
  line `transaction or arrangement referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115VZB, the Assessing Officer shall,`
  line `by an order in writing, exclude such company from the tonnage tax scheme:`
  line `Provided that an opportunity shall be given by the Assessing Officer by serving a notice calling upon`
  line `such company to show cause, on a date and time to be specified in the notice, why it should not be`
  line `excluded from the tonnage tax scheme:`
  line `Provided further that no order under this sub-section shall be passed without the previous approval of`
  line `the 1 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner].`
  line `( 2 ) The provisions of this section shall not apply where the company shows to the satisfaction of the`
  line `Assessing Officer that the transaction or arrangement was a bona fide commercial transaction and had not`
  line `been entered into for the purpose of obtaining tax advantage under this Chapter.`
  line `( 3 ) Where an order has been passed under sub-section ( 1 ) by the Assessing Officer excluding the`
  line `tonnage tax company from the tonnage tax scheme, the option for tonnage tax scheme shall cease to be in`
  line `force from the first day of the previous year in which the transaction or arrangement was entered into.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_523_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_524:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-524
  sectionNo (524)
  orderNo 524
  title `Page 524`
  content obj_root_law_sections_524_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_524_footnotes
  sourcePage 524
obj_root_law_sections_524_content:
  string
  line 524
  line `1 [CHAPTER XIIH`
  line `I NCOME -T AX ON F RINGE B ENEFITS`
  line `A. — Meaning of certain expressions`
  line `115W. Definitions. — In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “employer” means,—`
  line `( i ) a company;`
  line `( ii ) a firm;`
  line `2 [( iii ) an association of persons or a body of individuals, whether incorporated or not;]`
  line `( iv ) a local authority; and`
  line `( v ) every artificial juridical person, not falling within any of the preceding sub-clauses:`
  line `3 [Provided that any person eligible for exemption under clause ( 23C ) of section 10 or`
  line `registered under section 12AA or a political party registered under section 29A of the`
  line `Representation of the People Act, 1951 (43 of 1951) shall not be deemed to be an employer for`
  line `the purposes of this Chapter;]`
  line `( b ) “fringe benefit tax” or “tax” means the tax chargeable under section 115WA.`
  line `B. — Basis of charge`
  line `115WA. Charge of fringe benefit tax. — ( 1 ) In addition to the income-tax charged under this Act,`
  line `there shall be charged for every assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 2006,`
  line `additional income-tax (in this Act referred to as fringe benefit tax) in respect of the fringe benefits`
  line `provided or deemed to have been provided by an employer to his employees during the previous year at`
  line `the rate of thirty per cent on the value of such fringe benefits.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding that no income-tax is payable by an employer on his total income computed in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act, the tax on fringe benefits shall be payable by such employer.`
  line `115WB. Fringe benefits. — ( 1 ) For the purposes of this Chapter, “fringe benefits” means any`
  line `consideration for employment provided by way of —`
  line `( a ) any privilege, service, facility or amenity, directly or indirectly, provided by an employer,`
  line `whether by way of reimbursement or otherwise, to his employees (including former employee or`
  line `employees);`
  line `( b ) any free or concessional ticket provided by the employer for private journeys of his`
  line `employees or their family members; 4 ***`
  line `( c ) any contribution by the employer to an approved superannuation fund for 5 [employees; and]`
  line `5 [( d ) anyspecified security or sweat equity shares allotted or transferred, directly or indirectly, by`
  line `the employer free of cost or at concessional rate to his employees (including former employee or`
  line `employees).`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 55 of 2005, s. 6, for Clause ( iii ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).Earlier substituted by Act 18 of 2005, s. 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-`
  line `2006).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `4. The word “and” omitted by Act 22 of 2007, s. 38 (w.e.f. 1 -4-2008).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 38, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_524_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_525:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-525
  sectionNo (525)
  orderNo 525
  title `Page 525`
  content obj_root_law_sections_525_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_525_footnotes
  sourcePage 525
obj_root_law_sections_525_content:
  string
  line 525
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( i ) “specified security” means the securities as defined in clause ( h ) of section 2 of the`
  line `Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956) 1 [and, where employees' stock option`
  line `has been granted under any plan or scheme therefor, includes the securities offered under such`
  line `plan or scheme];`
  line `( ii ) “sweat equity shares” means equity shares issued by a company to its employees or`
  line `directors at a discount or for consideration other than cash for providing know-how or making`
  line `available rights in the nature of intellectual property rights or value additions, by whatever name`
  line called.]
  line `( 2 ) The fringe benefits shall be deemed to have been provided by the employer to his employees, if`
  line `the employer has, in the course of his business or profession (including any activity whether or not such`
  line `activity is carried on with the object of deriving income, profits or gains) incurred any expense on, or`
  line `made any payment for, the following purposes, namely: —`
  line `( A ) entertainment;`
  line `( B ) provision of hospitality of every kind by the employer to any person, whether by way of`
  line `provision of food or beverages or in any other manner whatsoever and whether or not such provision`
  line `is made by reason of any express or implied contract or custom or usage of trade but does not`
  line `include —`
  line `( i ) any expenditure on, or payment for, food or beverages provided by the employer to his`
  line `employees in office or factory;`
  line `( ii ) any expenditure on or payment through paid vouchers which are not transferable and`
  line `usable only at eating joints or outlets;`
  line `2 [( iii ) any expenditure on or payment through non-transferable pre-paid electronic meal card`
  line `usable only at eating joints or outlets and which fulfils such other conditions as may be`
  line prescribed;]
  line `( C ) conference (other than fee for participation by the employees in any conference).`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, any expenditure on conveyance, tour and travel`
  line `(including foreign travel), on hotel, or boarding and lodging in connection with any conference shall be`
  line `deemed to be expenditure incurred for the purposes of conference;`
  line `( D ) sales promotion including publicity:`
  line `Provided that any expenditure on advertisement, —`
  line `( i ) being the expenditure (including rental) on advertisement of any form in any print`
  line `(including journals, catalogues or price lists) or electronic media or transport system;`
  line `( ii ) being the expenditure on the holding of, or the participation in, any press conference or`
  line `business convention, fair or exhibition;`
  line `( iii ) being the expenditure on sponsorship of any sports event or any other event organised`
  line `by any Government agency or trade association or body;`
  line `( iv ) being the expenditure on the publication in any print or electronic media of any notice`
  line `required to be published by or under any law or by an order of a court or tribunal;`
  line `( v ) being the expenditure on advertisement by way of signs, art work, painting, banners,`
  line `awnings, direct mail, electric spectaculars, kiosks, hoardings, 3 [bill boards, display of products] or`
  line `by way of such other medium of advertisement; 4 ***`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 25, for “and includes employees’ stock option” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2008).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 25, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 38, for “bill boards” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2008).`
  line `4. The word “and” omitted by Act 21 of 2006, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
