obj_root_law_sections_527_content:
  string
  line 527
  line `( 3 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), the privilege, service, facility or amenity does not include`
  line `perquisites in respect of which tax is paid or payable by the employee 1 [or any benefit or amenity in the`
  line `nature of free or subsidised transport or any such allowance provided by the employer to his employees`
  line `for journeys by the employees from their residence to the place of work or such place of work to the place`
  line `of residence.]`
  line `115WC. Value of fringe benefits. — ( 1 ) For the purposes of this Chapter, the value of fringe benefits`
  line `shall be the aggregate of the following, namely: —`
  line `( a ) cost at which the benefits referred to in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115WB, is`
  line `provided by the employer to the general public as reduced by the amount, if any, paid by, or`
  line `recovered from, his employee or employees:`
  line `Provided that in a case where the expenses of the nature referred to in clause ( b ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115WB are included in any other clause of sub-section ( 2 ) of the said`
  line `section, the total expenses included under such other clause shall be reduced by the amount of`
  line `expenditure referred to in the said clause ( b ) for computing the value of fringe benefits;`
  line `2 [( b ) the amount of contribution, referred to in clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115WB,`
  line `which exceeds one lakh rupees in respect of each employee;]`
  line `3 [( ba ) the fair market value of the specified security or sweat equity shares referred to in clause`
  line `( d ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115WB, on the date on which the option vests with the employee as`
  line `reduced by the amount actually paid by, or recovered from, the employee in respect of such security`
  line `or shares.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( i ) “fair market value” means the value determined in accordance with the method as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Board;`
  line `( ii ) “option” means a right but not an obligation granted to an employee to apply for the`
  line `specified security or sweat equity shares at a predetermined price;]`
  line `( c ) twenty per cent of the expenses referred to in 4 [clauses ( A ) to ( L )] of sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 115WB;`
  line `( d ) fifty per cent of the expenses referred to in 5 [clauses ( M ) to ( P )] of sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 115WB;`
  line `6 [( e ) five per cent. of the expenses referred to in clause ( Q ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 115WB.]`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), —`
  line `( a ) in the case of an employer engaged in the business of hotel, the value of fringe benefits for`
  line `the purposes referred to in clause ( B ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 115WB shall be “five per cent.”`
  line `instead of “twenty per cent.” referred to in clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 1 );`
  line `6 [( aa ) in the case of an employer engaged in the business of carriage of passengers or goods by`
  line `aircraft, the value of fringe benefits for the purposes referred to in clause ( B ) of sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 115WB shall be “five per cent” instead of “twenty per cent” referred to in clause ( c ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 );`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 28. (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 29, ibid., for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 39 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 26, for “clauses (A) to (K)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2009).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 26, ibid., for “clauses (L) to (P)” (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
