obj_root_law_sections_528_content:
  string
  line 528
  line `( ab ) in the case of an employer engaged in the business of carriage of passengers or goods by`
  line `ship, the value of fringe benefits for the purposes referred to in clause ( B ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 115WB shall be “five per cent” instead of “twenty per cent.” referred to in clause ( c ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 );]`
  line `( b ) in the case of an employer engaged in the business of construction, the value of fringe`
  line `benefits for the purposes referred to in clause ( F ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 115WB shall be “five`
  line `per cent” instead of “twenty per cent” referred to in clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 1 );`
  line `( c ) in the case of an employer engaged in the business of manufacture or production of`
  line `pharmaceuticals, the value of fringe benefits for the purposes referred to in clauses ( F ) and ( G ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 115WB shall be “five per cent” instead of “twenty per cent” referred to in`
  line `clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 1 );`
  line `( d ) in the case of an employer engaged in the business of manufacture or production of computer`
  line `software, the value of fringe benefits for the purposes referred to in clauses ( F ) and ( G ) of sub-section`
  line `(2) of section 115WB shall be “five per cent” instead of “twenty per cent” referred to in clause ( c ) of`
  line `sub-section (1);`
  line `1 [( da ) in the case of an employer engaged in the business of carriage of passengers or goods by`
  line `aircraft, the value of fringe benefits for the purposes referred to in clause ( G ) of sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 115WB shall be “five per cent” instead of “twenty per cent” referred to in clause ( c ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 );`
  line `( db ) in the case of an employer engaged in the business of carriage of passengers or goods by`
  line `ship, the value of fringe benefits for the purposes referred to in clause ( G ) of sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 115WB shall be “five per cent” instead of “twenty per cent” referred to in clause ( c ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 );]`
  line `( e ) in the case of an employer engaged in the business of carriage of passengers or goods by`
  line `motor car, the value of fringe benefits for the purposes referred to in clause ( H ) of sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 115WB shall be “five per cent” instead of “twenty per cent” referred to in clause ( c ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 );`
  line `( f ) in the case of an employer engaged in the business of carriage of passengers or goods by`
  line `aircraft, the value of fringe benefits for the purposes referred to in clause ( 1 ) of sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 115WB shall be taken as Nil.`
  line `C. — Procedure for filing of return in respect of fringe benefits, assessment and payment of tax in respect`
  line thereof
  line `115WD. Return of fringe benefits. — ( 1 ) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in section`
  line `139, every employer who during a previous year has paid or made provision for payment of fringe`
  line `benefits to his employees, shall, on or before the due date, furnish or cause to be furnished a return of`
  line `fringe benefits to the Assessing Officer in the prescribed form and verified in the prescribed manner and`
  line `setting forth such other particulars as may be prescribed, in respect of the previous year.`
  line `Explanation. — In this sub- section, “due date” means,—`
  line `( a ) where the employer is —`
  line `( i ) a company; or`
  line `( ii ) a person (other than a company) whose accounts are required to be audited under this`
  line `Act or under any other law for the time being in force,`
  line `the 2 [30th day of September] of the assessment year;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 27, for “31st day of October” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_528_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_529:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-529
  sectionNo (529)
  orderNo 529
  title `Page 529`
  content obj_root_law_sections_529_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_529_footnotes
  sourcePage 529
obj_root_law_sections_529_content:
  string
  line 529
  line `( b ) in the case of any other employer, the 31st day of July of the assessment year.`
  line `( 2 ) In the case of any employer who, in the opinion of the Assessing Officer, is responsible for paying`
  line `fringe benefit tax under this Act and who has not furnished a return under sub-section ( 1 ), the Assessing`
  line `Officer may, after the due date, issue a notice to him and serve the same upon him, requiring him to`
  line `furnish within thirty days from the date of service of the notice, the return in the prescribed form and`
  line `verified in the prescribed manner and setting forth such other particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 3 ) Any employer responsible for paying fringe benefit tax who has not furnished a return within the`
  line `time allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) or within the time allowed under a notice issued under sub-section ( 2 ),`
  line `may furnish the return for any previous year, at any time before the expiry of one year from the end of the`
  line `relevant assessment year or before the completion of the assessment, whichever is earlier.`
  line `( 4 ) If any employer, having furnished a return under sub-section ( 1 ), or in pursuance of a notice`
  line `issued under sub-section ( 2 ), discovers any omission or any wrong statement therein, he may furnish a`
  line `revised return at any time before the expiry of one year from the end of the relevant assessment year or`
  line `before the completion of the assessment, whichever is earlier.`
  line `115WE. Assessment. — 1 [( 1 ) Where a return has been made under section 115WD, such return shall`
  line `be processed in the following manner, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the value of fringe benefits shall be computed after making the following adjustments,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( i ) any arithmetical error in the return; or`
  line `( ii ) an incorrect claim, if such incorrect claim is apparent from any information in the return;`
  line `( b ) the tax and interest, if any, shall be computed on the basis of the value of fringe benefits`
  line `computed under clause ( a );`
  line `( c ) the sum payable by, or the amount of refund due to, the assessee shall be determined after`
  line `adjustment of the tax and interest, if any, computed under clause ( b ) by any advance tax paid, any tax`
  line `paid on self-assessment and any amount paid otherwise by way of tax or interest;`
  line `( d ) an intimation shall be prepared or generated and sent to the assessee specifying the sum`
  line `determined to be payable by, or the amount of refund due to, the assessee under clause ( c ); and`
  line `( e ) the amount of refund due to the assessee in pursuance of the determination under clause ( c )`
  line `shall be granted to the assessee:`
  line `Provided that no intimation under this sub-section shall be sent after the expiry of one year from`
  line `the end of the financial year in which the return is made.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, —`
  line `( a ) “an incorrect claim apparent from any information in the return” shall mean a claim, on the`
  line `basis of an entry, in the return, —`
  line `( i ) of an item, which is inconsistent with another entry of the same or some other item in`
  line `such return;`
  line `( ii ) in respect of which the information required to be furnished to substantiate such entry`
  line `has not been so furnished under this Act; or`
  line `( iii ) in respect of a deduction or value of fringe benefits, where such deduction or value`
  line `exceeds specified statutory limit which may have been expressed as monetary amount or`
  line `percentage or ratio or fraction;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 28, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_529_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_530:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-530
  sectionNo (530)
  orderNo 530
  title `Page 530`
  content obj_root_law_sections_530_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_530_footnotes
  sourcePage 530
obj_root_law_sections_530_content:
  string
  line 530
  line `( b ) the acknowledgement of the return shall be deemed to be the intimation in a case where no`
  line `sum is payable by, or refundable to, the assessee under clause ( c ), and where no adjustment has been`
  line `made under clause ( a ).`
  line `( 1A ) For the purposes of processing of returns under sub-section ( 1 ), the Board may make a scheme`
  line `for centralised processing of returns with a view to expeditiously determining the tax payable by, or the`
  line `refund due to, the assessee as required under that sub-section.`
  line `( 1B ) Save as otherwise expressly provided, for the purpose of giving effect to the scheme made under`
  line `sub-section ( 1A ), the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that any of`
  line `the provisions of this Act relating to processing of returns shall not apply or shall apply with such`
  line `exceptions, modifications and adaptations as may be specified in that notification; so, however, that no`
  line `direction shall be issued 1 [after the 31st day of March, 2011].`
  line `( 1C ) Every notification issued under sub-section ( 1B ), along with the scheme made under`
  line `sub-section ( 1A ), shall, as soon as may be after the notification is issued, be laid before each House of`
  line Parliament.]
  line `( 2 ) Where a return has been furnished under section 115WD, the Assessing Officer shall, if he`
  line `considers it necessary or expedient to ensure that the assessee has not understated the value of fringe`
  line `benefits or has not underpaid the tax in any manner, serve on the assessee a notice requiring him on a date`
  line `to be specified therein, either to attend his office or to produce, or cause to be produced, any evidence on`
  line `which the assessee may rely in support of the return:`
  line `Provided that no notice under this sub-section shall be served on the assessee after the expiry of 2 [six`
  line `months from the end of the financial year] in which the return is furnished.`
  line `( 3 ) On the day specified in the notice issued under sub-section ( 2 ), or as soon afterwards as may be,`
  line `after hearing such evidence as the assessee may produce and such other evidence as the Assessing Officer`
  line `may require on specified points, and after taking into account all relevant material which he has gathered,`
  line `the Assessing Officer shall, by an order in writing, make an assessment of the value of the fringe benefits`
  line `paid or payable by the assessee, and determine the sum payable by him or refund of any amount due to`
  line `him on the basis of such assessment.`
  line `( 4 ) Where a regular assessment under sub-section ( 3 ) or section 115WF is made, —`
  line `( a ) any tax or interest paid by the assessee under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to have been`
  line `paid towards such regular assessment;`
  line `( b ) if no refund is due on regular assessment or the amount refunded under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `exceeds the amount refundable on regular assessment, the whole or the excess amount so refunded`
  line `shall be deemed to be tax payable by the assessee and the provisions of this Act shall apply`
  line accordingly.
  line `115WF. Best judgment assessment. — If any person, being an employer —`
  line `( a ) fails to make the return required under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115WD and has not made a`
  line `return under sub-section ( 3 ) or a revised return under sub-section ( 4 ) of that section, or`
  line `( b ) fails to comply with all the terms of a notice issued under sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 115WD or fails to comply with a direction issued under sub-section ( 2A ) of section 142, or`
  line `( c ) having made a return, fails to comply with all the terms of a notice issued under sub-`
  line `section ( 2 ) of section 115WE,`
  line `the Assessing Officer, after taking into account all relevant material which the Assessing Officer has`
  line `gathered, shall, after giving the assessee an opportunity of being heard, make the assessment of the fringe`
  line `benefits to the best of his judgment and determine the sum payable by the assessee on the basis of such`
  line `assessment:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 31, for “after the 31st day of March, 2010” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2010). Earlier substituted by Act 33 of`
  line `2009, s. 48 (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 28, for “twelve months from the end of the month” (w. e.f. 1-4-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_530_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_531:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-531
  sectionNo (531)
  orderNo 531
  title `Page 531`
  content obj_root_law_sections_531_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_531_footnotes
  sourcePage 531
obj_root_law_sections_531_content:
  string
  line 531
  line `Provided that such opportunity shall be given by the Assessing Officer by serving a notice calling`
  line `upon the assessee to show cause, on a date and time to be specified in the notice as to why the assessment`
  line `should not be completed to the best of his judgment:`
  line `Provided further that it shall not be necessary to give such opportunity in a case where a notice under`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 115WD has been issued prior to the making of an assessment under this section.`
  line `115WG. Fringe benefits escaping assessment. — If the Assessing Officer has reason to believe that`
  line `any fringe benefits chargeable to tax have escaped assessment for any assessment year, he may, subject to`
  line `the provisions of section 115WH, 150 and 153, assess or reassess such fringe benefits and also any other`
  line `fringe benefits chargeable to tax which have escaped assessment and which come to his notice`
  line `subsequently in the course of the proceedings under this section, for the assessment year concerned`
  line `(hereafter referred to as the relevant assessment year).`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, the following shall also be deemed to be cases where`
  line `fringe benefits chargeable to tax have escaped assessment, namely: —`
  line `( a ) where no return of fringe benefits has been furnished by the assessee;`
  line `( b ) where a return of fringe benefits has been furnished by the assessee but no assessment has`
  line `been made and it is noticed by the Assessing Officer that the assessee has understated the value of`
  line `fringe benefits in the return;`
  line `( c ) where an assessment has been made, but the fringe benefits chargeable to tax have been`
  line under-assessed.
  line `115WH. Issue of notice where fringe benefits have escaped assessment. — ( 1 ) Before making the`
  line `assessment or reassessment under section 115WG, the Assessing Officer shall serve on the assessee a`
  line `notice requiring him to furnish within such period as may be specified in the notice, a return of the fringe`
  line `benefits in respect of which he is assessable under this Chapter during the previous year corresponding to`
  line `the relevant assessment year, in the prescribed form and verified in the prescribed manner and setting`
  line `forth such other particulars as may be prescribed, and the provisions of this Chapter shall, so far as may`
  line `be, apply accordingly as if such return were a return required to be furnished under section 115WD.`
  line `( 2 ) The Assessing Officer shall, before issuing any notice under this section, record his reasons for`
  line `doing so.`
  line `( 3 ) No notice under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be issued for the relevant assessment year after the expiry of`
  line `six years from the end of the relevant assessment year.`
  line `Explanation. — In determining fringe benefits chargeable to tax which have escaped assessment for`
  line `the purposes of this sub-section, the provisions of the Explanation to section 115WG shall apply as they`
  line `apply for the purposes of that section.`
  line `( 4 ) In a case where an assessment under sub-section ( 3 ) of section 115WE or section 115WG has`
  line `been made for the relevant assessment year, no notice shall be issued under sub-section ( 1 ) by an`
  line `Assessing Officer, after the expiry of four years from the end of the relevant assessment year, unless the`
  line `1 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 2 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]`
  line `is satisfied, on the reasons recorded by the Assessing Officer, that it is a fit case for the issue of such`
  line notice.
  line `115WI. Payment of fringe benefit tax. — Notwithstanding that the regular assessment in respect of`
  line `any fringe benefits is to be made in a later assessment year, the tax on such fringe benefits shall be`
  line `payable in advance during any financial year, in accordance with the provisions of section 115WJ, in`
  line `respect of the fringe benefits which would be chargeable to tax for the assessment year immediately`
  line `following that financial year, such fringe benefits being hereafter in this Chapter referred to as the`
  line `“current fringe benefits”.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_531_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_532:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-532
  sectionNo (532)
  orderNo 532
  title `Page 532`
  content obj_root_law_sections_532_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_532_footnotes
  sourcePage 532
obj_root_law_sections_532_content:
  string
  line 532
  line `115WJ. Advance tax in respect of fringe benefits. — ( 1 ) Every assessee who is liable to pay`
  line `advance tax under section 115WI, shall on his own accord, pay advance tax on his current fringe benefits`
  line `calculated in the manner laid down in sub-section ( 2 ).`
  line `1 [( 2 ) Advance tax on the current fringe benefits shall be payable by —`
  line `( a ) all the companies, who are liable to pay the same in four instalments during each financial`
  line `year and the due date of each instalment and the amount of such instalment shall be as specified in`
  line `Table I below:`
  line `TABLE I`
  line `Due date of instalment Amount payable`
  line `On or before the 15th June Not less than fifteen per cent of such advance tax.`
  line `On or before the 15th`
  line September
  line `Not less than forty-five per cent of such advance tax`
  line `as reduced by the amount, if any, paid in the`
  line `earlier instalment.`
  line `On or before the 15th`
  line December
  line `Not less than seventy-five per cent of such advance`
  line `tax as reduced by the amount or amounts, if any,`
  line `paid in the earlier instalment or instalments.`
  line `On or before the 15th March The whole amount of such advance tax as reduced by`
  line `the amount or amounts, if any, paid in the earlier`
  line `instalment or instalments;`
  line `( b ) all the assessees (other than companies), who are liable to pay the same in three instalments`
  line `during each financial year and the due date of each instalment and the amount of such instalment`
  line `shall be as specified in Table II below:`
  line `TABLE II`
  line `Due date of instalment Amount payable`
  line `On or before the 15th September Not less than thirty per cent of such advance`
  line tax.
  line `On or before the 15th December Not less than sixty per cent of such advance`
  line `tax as reduced by the amount, if any, paid`
  line `in the earlier instalment.`
  line `On or before the 15th March The whole amount of such advance tax as`
  line `reduced by the amount or amounts, if any,`
  line `paid in the earlier instalment or`
  line instalments.
  line `( 3 ) Where an assessee, being a company, has failed to pay the advance tax payable by him on or`
  line `before the due date for any instalment or where the advance tax paid by him is less than the amount`
  line `payable by the due date, he shall be liable to pay simple interest calculated at the rate of —`
  line `( i ) one per cent per month, for three months on an amount by which the advance tax paid on or`
  line `before the 15th June of the financial year falls short of fifteen per cent of the advance tax payable;`
  line `( ii ) one per cent per month, for three months on an amount by which the advance tax paid on or`
  line `before the 15th September of the financial year falls short of forty-five per cent of the advance tax`
  line payable;
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 40, for sub-sections ( 2 ) and ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_532_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_533:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-533
  sectionNo (533)
  orderNo 533
  title `Page 533`
  content obj_root_law_sections_533_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_533_footnotes
  sourcePage 533
obj_root_law_sections_533_content:
  string
  line 533
  line `( iii ) one per cent. per month, for three months on an amount by which the advance tax paid on or`
  line `before the 15th December of the financial year falls short of seventy-five per cent. of the advance tax`
  line `payable; and`
  line `( iv ) one per cent. on an amount by which the advance tax paid on or before the 15th March of the`
  line `financial year falls short of hundred per cent. of the advance tax payable.`
  line `( 4 ) Where an assessee, being a person other than a company, has failed to pay the advance tax`
  line `payable by him on or before the due date for any instalment or where the advance tax paid by him is less`
  line `than the amount payable by the due date, he shall be liable to pay simple interest calculated at the rate`
  line `of —`
  line `( i ) one per cent. per month, for three months on an amount by which the advance tax paid on or`
  line `before the 15th September of the financial year falls short of thirty per cent. of the advance tax`
  line payable;
  line `( ii ) one per cent. per month, for three months on an amount by which the advance tax paid on or`
  line `before the 15th December of the financial year falls short of sixty per cent of the advance tax payable;`
  line and
  line `( iii ) one per cent. on an amount by which the advance tax paid on or before the 15th March of the`
  line `financial year falls short of hundred per cent. of the advance tax payable.`
  line `( 5 ) Where an assessee has failed to pay the advance tax payable by him during a financial year or`
  line `where the advance tax paid by him is less than ninety per cent. of the tax assessed under section 115WE`
  line `or section 115WF or section 115WG, the assessee shall be liable to pay simple interest at the rate of one`
  line `per cent. per month, for every month or part of a month comprised in the period from the 1st day of April`
  line `next following such financial year to the date of assessment of tax under section 115WE or section`
  line `115WF or section 115WG.]`
  line `115WK. Interest for default in furnishing return of fringe benefits. — ( 1 ) Where the return of`
  line `fringe benefits for any assessment year under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 3 ) of section 115WD or in`
  line `response to a notice under sub-section ( 2 ) of that section, is furnished after the due date, or is not`
  line `furnished, the employer shall be liable to pay simple interest at the rate of one per cent. for every month`
  line `or part of a month comprised in the period commencing on the date immediately following the due date,`
  line `and, —`
  line `( a ) where the return is furnished after the due date, ending on the date of furnishing of the return;`
  line or
  line `( b ) where no return has been furnished, ending on the date of completion of the assessment under`
  line `section 115WF,`
  line `on the amount of the tax on the value of fringe benefits as determined under sub-section ( 1 ) of section`
  line `115WE or regular assessment as reduced by the advance tax paid under section 115WJ.`
  line `Explanation 1. — In this section, “due date” means the date specified in the Explanation to`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115WD as applicable in the case of the employer.`
  line `Explanation 2. — Where, in relation to an assessment year, an assessment is made for the first time`
  line `under section 115WG, the assessment so made shall be regarded as a regular assessment for the purposes`
  line `of this section.`
  line `( 2 ) The provisions contained in sub-sections ( 2 ) to ( 4 ) of section 234A shall, so far as may be, apply`
  line `to this section.`
