obj_root_law_sections_534_content:
  string
  line 534
  line `1 [115WKA. Recovery of fringe benefit tax by the employer from the employee. —`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any agreement or scheme under which any specified security or`
  line `sweat equity shares referred to in clause ( d ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115WB has been allotted or`
  line `transferred, directly or indirectly, by the employer on or after the 1st day of April, 2007, it shall be lawful`
  line `for the employer to vary the agreement or scheme under which such specified security or sweat equity`
  line `shares has been allotted or transferred so as to recover from the employee the fringe benefit tax to the`
  line `extent to which such employer is liable to pay the fringe benefit tax in relation to the value of fringe`
  line `benefits provided to the employee and determined under clause ( ba ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section`
  line 115WC.]
  line `2 [115WKB. Deemed payment of tax by employee. — ( 1 ) Where an employer has paid any fringe`
  line `benefit tax with respect to allotment or transfer of specified security or sweat equity shares, referred to in`
  line `clause ( d ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115WB, and has recovered such tax subsequently from an`
  line `employee, it shall be deemed that the fringe benefit tax so recovered is the tax paid by such employee in`
  line `relation to the value of the fringe benefit provided to him only to the extent to which the amount thereof`
  line `relates to the value of the fringe benefit provided to such employee, as determined under clause ( ba ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115WC.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provisions of this Act, where the fringe benefit`
  line `tax recovered from the employee is deemed to be the tax paid by such employee under sub-section ( 1 ),`
  line `such employee shall, under this Act, not be entitled to claim —`
  line `( i ) any refund out of such payment of tax; or`
  line `( ii ) any credit of such payment of tax against tax liability on other income or against any other`
  line `tax liability.]`
  line `115WL. Application of other provisions of this Act. — Save as otherwise provided in this Chapter,`
  line `all other provisions of this Act shall, as far as may be, apply in relation to fringe benefits also.`
  line `3 [115WM. Chapter XII-H not to apply after a certain date. — Nothing contained in this Chapter`
  line `shall apply, in respect of any assessment for the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April,`
  line `2010 or any subsequent assessment year.]`
  line `CHAPTER XIII`
  line `I NCOME-TAX AUTHORITIES`
  line `A. — Appointment and control`
  line `4 [116. Income-tax authorities. — There shall be the following classes of income-tax authorities for`
  line `the purposes of this Act, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the Central Board of Direct Taxes constituted under the Central Boards of Revenue Act, 1963`
  line `(54 of 1963),`
  line `5 [( aa ) Principal Directors General of Income-tax or Principal Chief Commissioners of`
  line Income-tax,]
  line `( b ) Directors-General of Income-tax or Chief Commissioners of Income-tax,`
  line `5 [( ba ) Principal Directors of Income-tax or Principal Commissioners of Income-tax,]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 49 (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 30, for sections 116, 117 and 118 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
