obj_root_law_sections_535_content:
  string
  line 535
  line `( c ) Directors of Income-tax or Commissioners of Income-tax or Commissioners of Income-tax`
  line `(Appeals),`
  line `1 ( cc ) Additional Directors of Income-tax or Additional Commissioners of Income-tax or`
  line `Additional Commissioners of Income-tax (Appeals),`
  line `2 [( cca ) Joint Directors of Income-tax or Joint Commissioners of Income-tax,]`
  line `( d ) Deputy Directors of Income-tax or Deputy Commissioners of Income-tax or Deputy`
  line `Commissioners of Income-tax (Appeals),`
  line `( e ) Assistant Directors of Income-tax or Assistant Commissioners of Income-tax,`
  line `( f ) Income-tax Officers,`
  line `( g ) Tax Recovery Officers,`
  line `( h ) Inspectors of Income-tax.`
  line `117. Appointment of income-tax authorities. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may appoint such`
  line `persons as it thinks fit to be income-tax authorities.`
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ), and subject to the rules and orders of the`
  line `Central Government regulating the conditions of service of persons in public services and posts, the`
  line `Central Government may authorise the Board, or a 3 [Principal Director General or Director-General], a`
  line `4 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or a 5 [Principal Director or Director] or a`
  line `6 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] to appoint income-tax authorities below the rank of an`
  line `7 [Assistant Commissioner or Deputy Commissioner].`
  line `( 3 ) Subject to the rules and orders of the Central Government regulating the conditions of service of`
  line `persons in public services and posts, an income-tax authority authorised in this behalf by the Board may`
  line `appoint such executive or ministerial staff as may be necessary to assist it in the execution of its`
  line functions.
  line `118. Control of income-tax authorities. — The Board may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `direct that any income-tax authority or authorities specified in the notification shall be subordinate to such`
  line `other income-tax authority or authorities as may be specified in such notification.]`
  line `8 [119. Instructions to subordinate authorities. — ( 1 ) The Board may, from time to time, issue such`
  line `orders, instructions and directions to other income-tax authorities as it may deem fit for the proper`
  line `administration of this Act, and such authorities and all other persons employed in the execution of this`
  line `Act shall observe and follow such orders, instructions and directions of the Board:`
  line `Provided that no such orders, instructions or directions shall be issued —`
  line `( a ) so as to require any income-tax authority to make a particular assessment or to dispose of a`
  line `particular case in a particular manner; or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-6-1994).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 39 (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Director General” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Director” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 3, for “Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 25, for section 119 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
