obj_root_law_sections_536_content:
  string
  line 536
  line `( b ) so as to interfere with the discretion of the 1 *** 2 [Commissioner (Appeals)] in the exercise of`
  line `his appellate functions.`
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, —`
  line `( a ) the Board may, if it considers it necessary or expedient so to do, for the purpose of proper and`
  line `efficient management of the work of assessment and collection of revenue, issue, from time to time`
  line `(whether by way of relaxation of any of the provisions of sections 3 [115P, 115S, 115WD, 115WE,`
  line `115WF, 115WG, 115WH, 115WJ, 115WK,] 4 [139,] 143, 144, 147, 148, 154, 155`
  line `5 [, 158BFA], 6 [sub-section (1A) of section 201, sections 210, 211, 234A, 234B, 234C 7 [, 234E]],`
  line `8 [270A,] 271 9 [, 271C, 271CA] and 273 or otherwise), general or special orders in respect of 10 [any`
  line `class of incomes or fringe benefits] or class of cases, setting forth directions or instructions (not being`
  line `prejudicial to assessees) as to the guidelines, principles or procedures to be followed by other income-`
  line `tax authorities in the work relating to assessment or collection of revenue or the initiation of`
  line `proceedings for the imposition of penalties and any such order may, if the Board is of opinion that it`
  line `is necessary in the public interest so to do, be published and circulated in the prescribed manner for`
  line `general information;`
  line `( b ) the Board may, if it considers it desirable or expedient so to do for avoiding genuine hardship`
  line `in any case or class of cases, by general or special order, authorise 11 [any income-tax authority, not`
  line `being a 12 *** Commissioner (Appeals)] to admit an application or claim for any exemption,`
  line `deduction, refund or any other relief under this Act after the expiry of the period specified by or under`
  line `this Act for making such application or claim and deal with the same on merits in accordance with`
  line law;
  line `13 [( c ) the Board may, if it considers it desirable or expedient so to do for avoiding genuine`
  line `hardship in any case or class of cases, by general or special order for reasons to be specified therein,`
  line `relax any requirement contained in any of the provisions of Chapter IV or Chapter VI-A, where the`
  line `assessee has failed to comply with any requirement specified in such provision for claiming deduction`
  line `thereunder, subject to the following conditions, namely: —`
  line `( i ) the default in complying with such requirement was due to circumstances beyond the`
  line `control of the assessee; and`
  line `( ii ) the assessee has complied with such requirement before the completion of assessment in`
  line `relation to the previous year in which such deduction is claimed:`
  line `Provided that the Central Government shall cause every order issued under this clause to be`
  line `laid before each House of Parliament.]`
  line `14 * * * * *`
  line `1. The words and brackets “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or the” omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `Earlier amended by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and The Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978) and 4 of 1988, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1-4-`
  line `1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and The Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 38, for “sections 115P, 115S” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 55 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 42, for “210, 234A, 234B” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1991).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 46 (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 64 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 49 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 38, for “any class of incomes” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 31, for “the Commissioner or the Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `12. The words and brackets “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or the” omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line `13. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line `14. Sub-section ( 3 ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
