  content obj_root_law_sections_537_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_537_footnotes
  sourcePage 537
obj_root_law_sections_537_content:
  string
  line 537
  line `1 [ 120. Jurisdiction of income-tax authorities. — ( 1 ) Income-tax authorities shall exercise all or any`
  line `of the powers and perform all or any of the functions conferred on, or, as the case may be, assigned to`
  line `such authorities by or under this Act in accordance with such directions as the Board may issue for the`
  line `exercise of the powers and performance of the functions by all or any of those authorities.`
  line `2 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that any income-tax authority, being`
  line `an authority higher in rank, may, if so directed by the Board, exercise the powers and perform the`
  line `functions of the income-tax authority lower in rank and any such direction issued by the Board shall be`
  line `deemed to be a direction issued under sub-section ( 1 ).]`
  line `( 2 ) The directions of the Board under sub-section ( 1 ) may authorise any other income-tax authority to`
  line `issue orders in writing for the exercise of the powers and performance of the functions by all or any of the`
  line `other income-tax authorities who are subordinate to it.`
  line `( 3 ) In issuing the directions or orders referred to in sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ), the Board or other`
  line `income-tax authority authorised by it may have regard to any one or more of the following criteria,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( a ) territorial area;`
  line `( b ) persons or classes of persons;`
  line `( c ) incomes or classes of income; and`
  line `( d ) cases or classes of cases.`
  line `( 4 ) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ), the Board may, by general or`
  line `special order, and subject to such conditions, restrictions or limitations as may be specified therein, —`
  line `( a ) authorise any 3 [Principal Director General or Director General] or 4 [Principal Director or`
  line `Director] to perform such functions of any other income-tax authority as may be assigned to him by`
  line `the Board;`
  line `( b ) empower the 3 [Principal Director General or Director General] or 5 [Principal Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 6 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] to issue`
  line `orders in writing that the powers and functions conferred on, or as the case may be, assigned to, the`
  line `Assessing Officer by or under this Act in respect of any specified area or persons or classes of`
  line `persons or incomes or classes of income or cases or classes of cases, shall be exercised or performed`
  line `by 7 [an Additional Commissioner or] 8 [an Additional Director or] a 9 [Joint Commissioner] or a`
  line `10 [Joint Director]] and, where any order is made under this clause, references in any other provision of`
  line `this Act, or in any rule made thereunder to the Assessing Officer shall be deemed to be references to`
  line `such 11 [an Additional Commissioner or] 12 [Additional Director or] a 9 [Joint Commissioner] or 10 [Joint`
  line `Director] by whom the powers and functions are to be exercised or performed under such order, and`
  line `any provision of this Act requiring approval or sanction of the 9 [Joint Commissioner] shall not apply.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 32, for section 120 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 30 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1988)`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Director General” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Director” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Chief Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 42 (w.r.e.f. 1-6-1994).`
  line `8. Ins. by s. 42, ibid. (w.r.e.f. 1-10-1996).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 3, for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.r.e.f 1 -10-1998).`
  line `10. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for “Deputy Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `1 1. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 42 (w.r.e.f. 1-6-1994).`
  line `12. Ins. by s. 42, ibid. (w.r.e.f. 1-10-1996).`
obj_root_law_sections_537_footnotes:
