obj_root_law_sections_538_content:
  string
  line 538
  line `( 5 ) The directions and orders referred to in sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) may, wherever considered`
  line `necessary or appropriate for the proper management of the work, require two or more Assessing Officers`
  line `(whether or not of the same class) to exercise and perform, concurrently, the powers and functions in`
  line `respect of any area or persons or classes of persons or incomes or classes of income or cases or classes of`
  line `cases; and, where such powers and functions are exercised and performed concurrently by the Assessing`
  line `Officers of different classes, any authority lower in rank amongst them shall exercise the powers and`
  line `perform the functions as any higher authority amongst them may direct, and, further, references in any`
  line `other provision of this Act or in any rule made thereunder to the Assessing Officer shall be deemed to be`
  line `references to such higher authority and any provision of this Act requiring approval or sanction of any`
  line `such authority shall not apply.`
  line `( 6 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any direction or order issued under this section, or`
  line `in section 124, the Board may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that for the purpose of`
  line `furnishing of the return of income or the doing of any other act or thing under this Act or any rule made`
  line `thereunder by any person or class of persons, the income-tax authority exercising and performing the`
  line `powers and functions in relation to the said person or class of persons shall be such authority as may be`
  line `specified in the notification.]`
  line `[ 121. Jurisdiction of Commissioners. ] Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws ( Amendment ) Act 1987`
  line `(4 of 1987), s. 33 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).]`
  line `[ 121A. Jurisdiction of Commissioners (Appeals). ] Omitted by s. 33, ibid ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988). Original`
  line `section was inserted by the Financ e ( No. 2) Act, 1977 (29 of 1977), s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `( w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `[ 122. Jurisdiction of Appellate Assistant Commissioners. ] Omitted by s. 33, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `[ 123. Jurisdiction of Inspecting Assistant Commissioners. ] Omitted by s. 33, ibid. ( w.e.f. 1-4-`
  line `1988).`
  line `1 [ 124. Jurisdiction of Assessing Officers. — ( 1 ) Where by virtue of any direction or order issued`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) of section 120, the Assessing Officer has been vested with`
  line `jurisdiction over any area, within the limits of such area, he shall have jurisdiction —`
  line `( a ) in respect of any person carrying on a business or profession, if the place at which he carries`
  line `on his business or profession is situate within the area, or where his business or profession is carried`
  line `on in more places than one, if the principal place of his business or profession is situate within the`
  line `area, and`
  line `( b ) in respect of any other person residing within the area.`
  line `( 2 ) Where a question arises under this section as to whether an Assessing Officer has jurisdiction to`
  line `assess any person, the question shall be determined by the 2 [Principal Director General or Director`
  line `General] or the 3 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or the 4 [Principal Commissioner`
  line `or Commissioner]; or where the question is one relating to areas within the jurisdiction of`
  line `different 2 [Principal Director General or Director General] or 3 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner] or 4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner], by the 2 [Principal Director General or`
  line `Director General] or 3 [Principal Chief Commissioners or Chief Commissioners] or 4 [Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner] concerned or, if they are not in agreement, by the Board or by`
  line `such 2 [Principal Director General or Director General] or 3 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner] or 4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] as the Board may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, specify.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 34, for section 124 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 2 5 of 2014, s. 4, for “Director General” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Chief Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
