obj_root_law_sections_539_content:
  string
  line 539
  line `( 3 ) No person shall be entitled to call in question the jurisdiction of an Assessing Officer —`
  line `( a ) where he has made a return 1 [under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115WD or under sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) of section 139], after the expiry of one month from the date on which he was served with a notice`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142 or 2 [sub-section ( 2 ) of section 115WE or sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 143] or after the completion of the assessment, whichever is earlier;`
  line `( b ) where he has made no such return, after the expiry of the time allowed by the notice under`
  line `3 [sub-section ( 2 ) of section 115WD or sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142 or under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 115WH or under section 148 for the making of the return or by the notice under the first`
  line `proviso to section 115WF or under the first proviso to section 144] to show cause why the assessment`
  line `should not be completed to the best of the judgment of the Assessing Officer, whichever is earlier;`
  line `4 [( c ) where an action has been taken under section 132 or section 132A, after the expiry of one`
  line `month from the date on which he was served with a notice under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 153A or`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 153C or after the completion of the assessment, whichever is earlier. ]`
  line `( 4 ) Subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 3 ), where an assessee calls in question the jurisdiction of`
  line `an Assessing Officer, then the Assessing Officer shall, if not satisfied with the correctness of the claim,`
  line `refer the matter for determination under sub-section ( 2 ) before the assessment is made.`
  line `( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section or in any direction or order issued`
  line `under section 120, every Assessing Officer shall have all the powers conferred by or under this Act on an`
  line `Assessing Officer in respect of the income accruing or arising or received within the area, if any, over`
  line `which he has been vested with jurisdiction by virtue of the directions or orders issued under sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) of section 120.`
  line `[125. Powers of Commissioner respecting specified areas, cases, persons, etc.] Omitted by the`
  line `Direct Tax Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988), s. 33 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `[125A. Concurrent jurisdiction of Inspecting Assistant Commissioner and Income-tax`
  line `Officer.] Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988), s. 33 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `Original section was inserted by the Taxation Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1975, ( w.e.f. 1-10-1975).]`
  line `[126. Powers of Board respecting specified area, classes of persons or incomes.] Omitted by the`
  line `Direct Tax Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988), s. 33 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `127.Power to transfer cases. — ( 1 ) The 5 [Principal Director General or Director General]`
  line `or 6 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 7 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner] may, after giving the assessee a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter,`
  line `wherever it is possible to do so, and after recording his reasons for doing so, transfer any case from one or`
  line `more Assessing Officers subordinate to him (whether with or without concurrent jurisdiction) to any other`
  line `Assessing Officer or Assessing Officers (whether with or without concurrent jurisdiction) also`
  line `subordinate to him.`
  line `( 2 ) Where the Assessing Officer or Assessing Officers from whom the case is to be transferred and`
  line `the Assessing Officer or Assessing Officers to whom the case is to be transferred are not subordinate to`
  line `the same 5 [Principal Director General or Director General] or 6 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner] or 7 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner], —`
  line `( a ) where the 5 [Principal Director General or Director General] or 6 [Principal Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 7 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] to whom such`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 39, for “under sub -section ( 1 ) of section 139” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 39, ibid., for “sub -section ( 2 ) of section 143” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 39, ibid., for “sub -section ( 1 ) of section 142 or under section 148 for the making of the return or by the notice`
  line `under the first proviso to section 144” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Director General” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Chief Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
