obj_root_law_sections_540_content:
  string
  line 540
  line `Assessing Officers are subordinate are in agreement, then the 1 [Principal Director General or Director`
  line `General] or 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 3 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner] from whose jurisdiction the case is to be transferred may, after giving the assessee a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter, wherever it is possible to do so, and after`
  line `recording his reasons for doing so, pass the order;`
  line `( b ) where the 1 [Principal Directors General or Directors General] or 2 [Principal Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 3 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] aforesaid are`
  line `not in agreement, the order transferring the case may, similarly, be passed by the Board or any`
  line `such 1 [Principal Director General or Director General] or 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner] or 3 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] as the Board may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, authorise in this behalf.`
  line `( 3 ) Nothing in sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) shall be deemed to require any such opportunity to`
  line `be given where the transfer is from any Assessing Officer or Assessing Officers (whether with or without`
  line `concurrent jurisdiction) to any other Assessing Officer or Assessing Officers (whether with or without`
  line `concurrent jurisdiction) and the offices of all such officers are situated in the same city, locality or place.`
  line `( 4 ) The transfer of a case under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) may be made at any stage of the`
  line `proceedings, and shall not render necessary the re-issue of any notice already issued by the Assessing`
  line `Officer or Assessing Officers from whom the case is transferred.]`
  line `Explanation. — In section 120 and this section, the word “case”, in relation to any person whose name`
  line `is specified in any order or direction issued thereunder, means all proceedings under this Act in respect of`
  line `any year which may be pending on the date of such order or direction or which may have been completed`
  line `on or before such date, and includes also all proceedings under this Act which may be commenced after`
  line `the date of such order or direction in respect of any year.`
  line `[128. Functions of Inspectors of Income-tax.] Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws ( Amendment ) Act,`
  line `1987 (4 of 1988), s. 33 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `129. Change of incumbent of an office. — Whenever in respect of any proceeding under this Act an`
  line `income-tax authority ceases to exercise jurisdiction and is succeeded by another who has and exercises`
  line `jurisdiction, the income-tax authority so succeeding may continue the proceeding from the stage at which`
  line `the proceeding was left by his predecessor:`
  line `Provided that the assessee concerned may demand that before the proceeding is so continued the`
  line `previous proceeding or any part thereof be reopened or that before any order of assessment is passed`
  line `against him, he be reheard.`
  line `[130. Commissioner competent to perform any function or functions. ] Omitted by the Direct Tax`
  line `Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988), s. 33 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `[130A. Income-tax Officer competent to perform any function or functions. ] Omitted by the`
  line `Direct Tax Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988), s. 33 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988). Original section was`
  line `inserted by the Finance ( No. 2) Act, 1967 (20 of 1967), s. 27 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1967).`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Director General” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Chief Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
