obj_root_law_sections_541_content:
  string
  line 541
  line `131. Power regarding discovery, production of evidence, etc. — ( 1 ) The 1 [Assessing Officer],`
  line `2 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)], 3 [,Commissioner (Appeals) 4 [, 5 [Principal Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Chief Commissioner or 6 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] and Dispute Resolution Panel`
  line `referred to in clause ( a ) of sub-section (15) of section 144C]] shall, for the purposes of this Act, have the`
  line `same powers as are vested in a court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), when trying a`
  line `suit in respect of the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) discovery and inspection;`
  line `( b ) enforcing the attendance of any person, including any officer of a banking company and`
  line `examining him on oath;`
  line `( c ) compelling the production of books of account and other documents; and`
  line `( d ) issuing commissions.`
  line `7 [( 1A ) 8 [If the 9 [Principal Director General or Director General] or 10 [Principal Director or Director]`
  line `or 11 [Joint Director] or 12 [Assistant Director or Deputy Director], or the authorised officer referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 132 before he takes action under clauses ( i ) to ( v ) of that sub-section,] has`
  line `reason to suspect that any income has been concealed, or is likely to be concealed, by any person or class`
  line `of persons, within his jurisdiction, then, for the purposes of making any enquiry or investigation relating`
  line `thereto, it shall be competent for him to exercise the powers conferred under sub-section ( 1 ) on the`
  line `income-tax authorities referred to in that sub-section, notwithstanding that no proceedings with respect to`
  line `such person or class of persons are pending before him or any other income-tax authority.`
  line `13 [( 2 ) For the purpose of making an inquiry or investigation in respect of any person or class of`
  line `persons in relation to an agreement referred to in section 90 or section 90A, it shall be competent for any`
  line `income-tax authority not below the rank of Assistant Commissioner of Income-tax, as may be notified by`
  line `the Board in this behalf, to exercise the powers conferred under sub-section ( 1 ) on the income-tax`
  line `authorities referred to in that sub-section, notwithstanding that no proceedings with respect to such person`
  line `or class of persons are pending before it or any other income-tax authority.]`
  line `( 3 ) Subject to any rules made in this behalf, any authority referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) 7 [or`
  line `sub-section ( 1A )] 13 [or sub-section ( 2 )] may impound and retain in its custody for such period as it thinks`
  line `fit any books of account or other documents produced before it in any proceeding under this Act:`
  line `Provided that 14 [an 15 [Assessing Officer] or an 16 [Assistant Director or Deputy Director]] shall not —`
  line `( a ) impound any books of account or other documents without recording his reasons for so`
  line `doing, or`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 3 and the Fifth Schedule, for “and Commissioner” (w.e.f. 10 -7-1978).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 50, for “and Chief Commissioner or Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2009).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 33, for “If the Assistant Director of Inspection” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1988).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Director General” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `10. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Director” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 3, for “Deputy Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `12. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for “Assistant Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `13. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-6-2011).`
  line `14. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 34, for “an Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1975).`
  line `15. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `16. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 3, for “Assistant Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998). Earlier su bstituted as “Assistant Director” by`
  line `Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Assistant Director of Inspection” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
