obj_root_law_sections_542_content:
  string
  line 542
  line `( b ) retain in his custody any such books or documents for a period exceeding fifteen days`
  line `(exclusive of holidays) without obtaining the approval of 1 [ the 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Chief Commissioner] or 3 [Principal Director General or Director General] or 4 [Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner ]or 5 [Principal Director or Director] therefor, as the case may be.]`
  line `6 [132. Search and seizure. — ( 1 ) Where the 7 [ 3 [Principal Director General or Director General] or`
  line `5 [Principal Director or Director]] or the 8 [ 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or`
  line `4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] 9 [or Additional Director or Additional Commissioner] 10 [or`
  line `Joint Director or Joint Commissioner] in consequence of information in his possession, has reason to`
  line `believe that —`
  line `( a ) any person to whom a summons under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 37 of the Indian Income-tax`
  line `Act, 1922 (11 of 1922), or under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 131 of this Act, or a notice under`
  line `sub-section ( 4 ) of section 22 of the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922, or under sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 142 of this Act was issued to produce, or cause to be produced, any books of account or other`
  line `documents has omitted or failed to produce, or cause to be produced, such books of account or other`
  line `documents as required by such summons or notice, or`
  line `( b ) any person to whom a summons or notice as aforesaid has been or might be issued will not,`
  line `or would not, produce or cause to be produced, any books of account or other documents which will`
  line `be useful for, or relevant to, any proceeding under the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922), or`
  line `under this Act, or`
  line `( c ) any person is in possession of any money, bullion, jewellery or other valuable article or thing`
  line `and such money, bullion, jewellery or other valuable article or thing represents either wholly or partly`
  line `income or property 11 [which has not been, or would not be, disclosed] for the purposes of the Indian`
  line `Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922), or this Act (hereinafter in this section referred to as the`
  line `undisclosed income or property),`
  line `12 [then, —`
  line `( A ) the 7 [ 3 [Principal Director General or Director General] or 5 [Principal Director or Director] or`
  line `the 8 [ 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 4 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner], as the case may be, may authorise any 13 [Additional Director or Additional`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 33, for “the Chief Commissioner or Commissioner therefor” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1988). Earlier`
  line `substituted as “Chief Commissioner or Commissioner” for “Commissioner” by 4 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Director General” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., f or “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Director” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 1 of 1965, s. 2, for section 132 (w.e.f. 12-3-1965).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Director of Inspection” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act s. 2, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 51, for “or any such Joint Director or Joint Commissioner as may be empowered in this behalf`
  line `by the Board,” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1994). Earlier amended by Act 41 of 1975, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975), 21 of 1998, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-`
  line `10-1998) and 4 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `10. Ins. by s. 51, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 35, for “which has not been disclosed” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1975).`
  line `12. Subs. by s. 35, ibid., for “he may authorise any Deputy Director of Inspection, Inspecting Assistant Commissioner,`
  line `Assistant Director of Inspection or Income-tax Officer (hereinafter referred to as the authorized officer) to —” (w.e.f. 1 -`
  line `10-1975).`
  line `13. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 51 (w.e.f. 1-6-1994).`
