obj_root_law_sections_544_content:
  string
  line 544
  line `1 [Provided that where any building, place, vessel, vehicle or aircraft referred to in clause ( i ) is within`
  line `the area of jurisdiction of any 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 3 [Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner], but such 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or`
  line `3 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] has no jurisdiction over the person referred to in clause ( a )`
  line `or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ), then, notwithstanding anything contained in 4 [section 120], it shall be`
  line `competent for him to exercise the powers under this sub-section in all cases where he has reason to`
  line `believe that any delay in getting the authorisation from the 5 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner] or 6 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] having jurisdiction over such person may`
  line `be prejudicial to the interests of the revenue:]`
  line `7 [Provided further that where it is not possible or practicable to take physical possession of any`
  line `valuable article or thing and remove it to a safe place due to its volume, weight or other physical`
  line `characteristics or due to its being of a dangerous nature, the authorised officer may serve an order on the`
  line `owner or the person who is in immediate possession or control thereof that he shall not remove, part with`
  line `or otherwise deal with it, except with the previous permission of such authorised officer and such action`
  line `of the authorised officer shall be deemed to be seizure of such valuable article or thing under clause ( iii ):]`
  line `8 [Provided also that nothing contained in the second proviso shall apply in case of any valuable article`
  line `or thing, being stock-in-trade of the business:]`
  line `9 [Provided also that no authorisation shall be issued by the Additional Director or Additional`
  line `Commissioner or Joint Director or Joint Commissioner on or after the 1st day of October, 2009 unless he`
  line `has been empowered by the Board to do so.]`
  line `10 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the reason to believe, as`
  line `recorded by the income-tax authority under this sub-section, shall not be disclosed to any person or any`
  line `authority or the Appellate Tribunal.]`
  line `11 [( 1A ) Where any 5 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 6 [Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner], in consequence of information in his possession, has reason to suspect`
  line `that any books of account, other documents, money, bullion, jewellery or other valuable article or thing in`
  line `respect of which an officer has been authorised by the 12 [Principal Director General or Director General]`
  line `or 13 [Principal Director or Director] or any other 5 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner]`
  line `or 6 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] or 14 [Additional Director or Additional Commissioner]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 35(w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6- 2013). Earlier substituted as “Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner” by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6- 2013). Earlier substituted as “Chief Commissioner or Commissioner”`
  line `by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 37, for “section 121” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 2 5 of 2014, s. 4, “Chief Commissioner or Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6- 2013). Earlier substituted as “Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner” for “Commissioner” by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 59 (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 51 (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `11. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `12. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Director General” (w.e.f. 1 -6- 2013). Earlier substituted as “Director General or`
  line `Director” for “Director of Inspection” by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `13. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Director” (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
  line `14. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 51, for “any such Joint Director or Joint Commissioner as may be empowered in this behalf`
  line `by the Board” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1994).`
