obj_root_law_sections_545_content:
  string
  line 545
  line `1 [or Joint Director or Joint Commissioner] to take action under clauses ( i ) to ( v ) of sub-section ( 1 ) are or`
  line `is kept in any building, place, vessel, vehicle or aircraft not mentioned in the authorisation under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ), such 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 3 [Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner] may, notwithstanding anything contained in 4 [section 120], authorise`
  line `the said officer to take action under any of the clauses aforesaid in respect of such building, place, vessel,`
  line `vehicle or aircraft.]`
  line `5 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the reason to suspect, as`
  line `recorded by the income-tax authority under this sub-section, shall not be disclosed to any person or any`
  line `authority or the Appellate Tribunal.]`
  line `( 2 ) The authorised officer may requisition the services of any police officer or of any officer of the`
  line `Central Government, or of both, to assist him for all or any of the purposes specified in sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `6 [or sub-section ( 1A )] and it shall be the duty of every such officer to comply with such requisition.`
  line `( 3 ) The authorised officer may, where it is not practicable to seize any such books of account, other`
  line `documents, money, bullion, jewellery or other valuable article or thing, 7 [for reasons other than those`
  line `mentioned in the second proviso to sub-section ( 1 ),] serve an order on the owner or the person who is in`
  line `immediate possession or control thereof that he shall not remove, part with or otherwise deal with it`
  line `except with the previous permission of such officer and such officer may take such steps as may be`
  line `necessary for ensuring compliance with this sub-section.`
  line `8 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that serving of an order as aforesaid`
  line `under this sub-section shall not be deemed to be seizure of such books of account, other documents,`
  line `money, bullion, jewellery or other valuable article or thing under clause ( iii ) of sub-section ( 1 ).]`
  line `( 4 ) The authorised officer may, during the course of the search or seizure, examine on oath any`
  line `person who is found to be in possession or control of any books of account, documents, money, bullion,`
  line `jewellery or other valuable article or thing and any statement made by such person during such`
  line `examination may thereafter be used in evidence in any proceeding under the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922`
  line `(11 of 1922), or under this Act.`
  line `8 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the examination of any person`
  line `under this sub-section may be not merely in respect of any books of account, other documents or assets`
  line `found as a result of the search, but also in respect of all matters relevant for the purposes of any`
  line `investigation connected with any proceeding under the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922), or`
  line `under this Act.]`
  line `6 [( 4A ) Where any books of account, other documents, money, bullion, jewellery or other valuable`
  line `article or thing are or is found in the possession or control of any person in the course of a search, it may`
  line `be presumed —`
  line `( i ) that such books of account, other documents, money, bullion, jewellery or other valuable`
  line `article or thing belong or belongs to such person;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 51, (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6- 2013). Earlier substituted as “Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner” for “Commissioner” by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 37, for “section 121” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
