obj_root_law_sections_546_content:
  string
  line 546
  line `( ii ) that the contents of such books of account and other documents are true; and`
  line `( iii ) that the signature and every other part of such books of account and other documents which`
  line `purport to be in the handwriting of any particular person or which may reasonably be assumed to`
  line `have been signed by, or to be in the handwriting of, any particular person, are in that person's`
  line `handwriting, and in the case of a document stamped, executed or attested, that it was duly stamped`
  line `and executed or attested by the person by whom it purports to have been so executed or attested.]`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `( 8 ) The books of account or other documents seized under sub-section ( 1 ) 2 [or sub-section ( 1A )] shall`
  line `not be retained by the authorised officer for a period exceeding 3 [thirty days from the date of the order of`
  line `assessment under 4 [section 153A or clause ( c ) of section 158BC]] unless the reasons for retaining the`
  line `same are recorded by him in writing and the approval of the 5 [ 6 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner], 7 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner], 8 [Principal Director General or Director`
  line `General] or 9 [Principal Director or Director]] for such retention is obtained:`
  line `Provided that the 5 [ 6 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner], 7 [Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner], 8 [Principal Director General or Director General] or 9 [Principal`
  line `Director or Director]] shall not authorise the retention of the books of account and other documents for a`
  line `period exceeding thirty days after all the proceedings under the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of`
  line `1922), or this Act in respect of the years for which the books of account or other documents are relevant`
  line `are completed.`
  line `10 [( 8A ) An order under sub-section ( 3 ) shall not be in force for a period exceeding sixty days from the`
  line `date of the order.]`
  line `( 9 ) The person from whose custody any books of account or other documents are seized under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) 2 [or sub-section ( 1A )] may make copies thereof, or take extracts therefrom, in the presence`
  line `of the authorised officer or any other person empowered by him in this behalf, at such place and time as`
  line `the authorised officer may appoint in this behalf.`
  line `11 [( 9A ) Where the authorised officer has no jurisdiction over the person referred to in clause ( a ) or`
  line `clause ( b ) or clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 1 ), the books of account or other documents, or any money,`
  line `bullion, jewellery or other valuable article or thing (hereafter in this section and in sections`
  line `132A and 132B referred to as the assets) seized under that sub-section shall be handed over by the`
  line `authorised officer to the Assessing Officer having jurisdiction over such person within a period of sixty`
  line `days from the date on which the last of the authorisations for search was executed and thereupon the`
  line `powers exercisable by the authorised officer under sub-section ( 8 ) or sub-section ( 9 ) shall be exercisable`
  line `by such Assessing Officer.]`
  line `12 [( 9B ) Where, during the course of the search or seizure or within a period of sixty days from the`
  line `date on which the last of the authorisations for search was executed, the authorised officer, for reasons to`
  line `1. Sub-sections ( 5 ) to ( 7 ) omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 56 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 56, for “one hundred and eighty days from the date of the seizure” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2002).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 59, for “under clause ( c ) of section 158BC” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2003).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 41, for “Chief Commissioner or Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1996).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Director General” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `9. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Director” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 56, for sub-section ( 8A ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `11. Subs. by s. 56, ibid., for sub-section ( 9A ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `12. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
