obj_root_law_sections_547_content:
  string
  line 547
  line `be recorded in writing, is satisfied that for the purpose of protecting the interest of revenue, it is necessary`
  line `so to do, he may with the previous approval of the Principal Director General or Director General or the`
  line `Principal Director or Director, by order in writing, attach provisionally any property belonging to the`
  line `assessee, and for the said purpose, the provisions of the Second Schedule shall, mutatis mutandis, apply.`
  line `( 9C ) Every provisional attachment made under sub-section ( 9B ) shall cease to have effect after the`
  line `expiry of a period of six months from the date of the order referred to in sub-section ( 9B ).`
  line `( 9D ) The authorised officer may, during the course of the search or seizure or within a period of sixty`
  line `days from the date on which the last of the authorisations for search was executed, make a reference to a`
  line `Valuation Officer referred to in section 142A, who shall estimate the fair market value of the property in`
  line `the manner provided under that section and submit a report of the estimate to the said officer within a`
  line `period of sixty days from the date of receipt of such reference.]`
  line `( 10 ) If a person legally entitled to the books of account or other documents seized under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) 1 [or sub-section (1A)] objects for any reason to the approval given by the 2 [ 3 [Principal`
  line `Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner], 4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner], 5 [Principal`
  line `Director General or Director General] or 6 [Principal Director or Director]] under sub-section ( 8 ), he may`
  line `make an application to the Board stating therein the reasons for such objection and requesting for the`
  line `return of the books of account or other documents 7 [and the Board may, after giving the applicant an`
  line `opportunity of being heard, pass such orders as it thinks fit].`
  line `8 * * * * *`
  line `9 [( 13 ) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), relating to searches and`
  line `seizure shall apply, so far as may be, to searches and seizure under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 1A ).]`
  line `( 14 ) The Board may make rules in relation to any search or seizure under this section; in particular,`
  line `and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for the procedure`
  line `to be followed by the authorised officer —`
  line `( i ) for obtaining ingress into 10 [any building, place, vessel, vehicle or aircraft] to be searched`
  line `where free ingress thereto is not available;`
  line `( ii ) for ensuring safe custody of any books of account or other documents or assets seized.`
  line `11 [ Explanation 1. — For the purposes of sub-sections ( 9A ), ( 9B ) and ( 9D ), with respect to “execution`
  line `of an authorisation for search”, the provisions of sub -section (2) of section 153B shall apply.]`
  line `Explanation 2. — In this section, the word “proceeding” means any proceeding in respect of any year,`
  line `whether under the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922), or this Act, which may be pending on the`
  line `date on which a search is authorised under this section or which may have been completed on or before`
  line `such date and includes also all proceedings under this Act which may be commenced after such date in`
  line `respect of any year.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 41, for “Chief Commissioner or Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1-10-1996).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Director General” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., fo r “Director” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 56 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `8. Sub-sections ( 11 ), ( 11A ) and ( 12 ) omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 56 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 35, for sub-section ( 13 ) (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `10. Subs. by s. 35, ibid., for “such building or place” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1975).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 50, for Explanation 1 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
