obj_root_law_sections_548_content:
  string
  line 548
  line `1 [ 132A. Powers to requisition books of account, etc. — ( 1 ) Where the 2 [ 3 [Principal Director General`
  line `or Director General] or 4 [Principal Director or Director]] or the 5 [ 6 [Principal Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Chief Commissioner] or 7 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]], in consequence of information in`
  line `his possession, has reason to believe that —`
  line `( a ) any person to whom a summons under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 37 of the Indian Income-tax`
  line `Act, 1922 (11 of 1922), or under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 131 of this Act, or a notice under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 22 of the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922, or under sub-section (1) of section`
  line `142 of this Act was issued to produce, or cause to be produced, any books of account or other`
  line `documents has omitted or failed to produce, or cause to be produced, such books of account or other`
  line `documents, as required by such summons or notice and the said books of account or other documents`
  line `have been taken into custody by any officer or authority under any other law for the time being in`
  line `force, or`
  line `( b ) any books of account or other documents will be useful for, or relevant to, any proceeding`
  line `under the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922), or under this Act and any person to whom a`
  line `summons or notice as aforesaid has been or might be issued will not, or would not, produce or cause`
  line `to be produced, such books of account or other documents on the return of such books of account or`
  line `other documents by any officer or authority by whom or which such books of account or other`
  line `documents have been taken into custody under any other law for the time being in force, or`
  line `( c ) any assets represent either wholly or partly income or property which has not been, or would`
  line `not have been, disclosed for the purposes of the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922), or this Act`
  line `by any person from whose possession or control such assets have been taken into custody by any`
  line `officer or authority under any other law for the time being in force,`
  line `then, the 2 [ 3 [Principal Director General or Director General] or 8 [Principal Director or Director]] or the`
  line `5 [ 6 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 7 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner]] may authorise any 9 [Additional Director, Additional Commissioner,] 10 [Joint Director],`
  line `11 [Joint Commissioner], 12 [Assistant Director or Deputy Director] or 13 [Assessing Officer] [hereafter in`
  line `this section and in sub-section ( 2 ) of section 278D referred to as the requisitioning officer] to require the`
  line `officer or authority referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ), as the case may be, to deliver such`
  line `books of account, other documents or assets to the requisitioning officer.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Director of Inspection” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Director General” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Director” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 25 o f 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Director” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 52 (w.e.f. 1-6-1994).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 2 1 of 1998, s. 3, for “Deputy Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10- 1998). Earlier substituted as “Deputy Director” by`
  line `Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Deputy Director of Inspection” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `11. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10- 1998). Earlier substituted as “Deputy Commissioner” by`
  line `Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Inspecting Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `12. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for “Assistant Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10- 1998). Earlier substituted as “Assistant Director” by`
  line `Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 for “Assistant Director of Inspection” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `13. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
