obj_root_law_sections_549_content:
  string
  line 549
  line `1 [ Explanation: — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the reason to believe, as`
  line `recorded y the income-tax authority under this sub-section, shall not be disclosed to any person or any`
  line `authority or the Appellate Tribunal.]`
  line `( 2 ) On a requisition being made under sub-section ( 1 ), the officer or authority referred to in clause ( a )`
  line `or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ), as the case may be, of that sub-section shall deliver the books of account, other`
  line `documents or assets to the requisitioning officer either forthwith or when such officer or authority is of`
  line `the opinion that it is no longer necessary to retain the same in his or its custody.`
  line `( 3 ) Where any books of account, other documents or assets have been delivered to the requisitioning`
  line `officer, the provisions of sub-sections ( 4A ) to ( 14 ) (both inclusive) of section 132 and section 132B shall,`
  line `so far as may be, apply as if such books of account, other documents or assets had been seized under sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ) of section 132 by the requisitioning officer from the custody of the person referred to in clause`
  line `( a ) or clause (b) or clause ( c ), as the case may be, of sub-section ( 1 ) of this section and as if for the words`
  line `“the authorised officer” occurring in any of th e aforesaid sub-sections ( 4A ) to ( 14 ), the words “the`
  line `requisitioning officer” were substituted.]`
  line `2 [ 3 [132B]. Application of seized or requisitioned assets. — ( 1 ) The assets seized under section`
  line `132 or requisitioned under section 132A may be dealt with in the following manner, namely: —`
  line `( i ) the amount of any existing liability under this Act, the Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957), the`
  line `Expenditure-tax Act, 1987 (35 of 1987), the Gift-tax Act, 1958 (18 of 1958) and the Interest-tax Act,`
  line `1974 (45 of 1974), and the amount of the liability determined on completion of the assessment`
  line `4 [under section 153A and the assessment of the year relevant to the previous year in which search is`
  line `initiated or requisition is made, or the amount of liability determined on completion of the assessment`
  line `under Chapter XIV-B for the block period, as the case may be] (including any penalty levied or`
  line `interest payable in connection with such assessment) and in respect of which such person is in default`
  line `or is 5 [deemed to be in default, or the amount of liability arising on an application made before the`
  line `Settlement Commission under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 245C, may be recovered out of such assets]:`
  line `6 [Provided that where the person concerned makes an application to the Assessing Officer within`
  line `thirty days from the end of the month in which the asset was seized, for release of asset and the nature`
  line `and source of acquisition of any such asset is explained] to the satisfaction of the Assessing Officer,`
  line `the amount of any existing liability referred to in this clause may be recovered out of such asset and`
  line `the remaining portion, if any, of the asset may be released, with the prior approval of the 7 [Principal`
  line `Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 8 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner], to the`
  line `person from whose custody the assets were seized:`
  line `Provided further that such asset or any portion thereof as is referred to in the first proviso shall be`
  line `released within a period of one hundred and twenty days from the date on which the last of the`
  line `authorisations for search under section 132 or for requisition under section 132A, as the case may be,`
  line `was executed:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 51 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `2. Section 132A renumbered as section 132B thereof by Act 41 of 1975, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 57, for section 132B (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 60, for “under Chapter XIVB for the block period” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2003).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 34, for “deemed to be in default, may be recovered out of such assets” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2015).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 60, for “Provided that where the nature and source of acquisition of any such asset is`
  line `explained” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2003).`
  line `7. Su bs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
