obj_root_law_sections_550_content:
  string
  line 550
  line `( ii ) if the assets consist solely of money, or partly of money and partly of other assets, the`
  line `Assessing Officer may apply such money in the discharge of the liabilities referred to in clause ( i ) and`
  line `the assessee shall be discharged of such liability to the extent of the money so applied;`
  line `( iii ) the assets other than money may also be applied for the discharge of any such liability`
  line `referred to in clause ( i ) as remains undischarged and for this purpose such assets shall be deemed to`
  line `be under distraint as if such distraint was effected by the Assessing Officer or, as the case may be, the`
  line `Tax Recovery Officer under authorisation from the 1 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner] or 2 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] under sub-section ( 5 ) of section`
  line `226 and the Assessing Officer or, as the case may be, the Tax Recovery Officer may recover the`
  line `amount of such liabilities by the sale of such assets and such sale shall be effected in the manner laid`
  line `down in the Third Schedule.`
  line `( 2 ) Nothing contained in sub-section ( 1 ) shall preclude the recovery of the amount of liabilities`
  line `aforesaid by any other mode laid down in this Act.`
  line `( 3 ) Any assets or proceeds thereof which remain after the liabilities referred to in clause ( i ) of sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ) are discharged shall be forthwith made over or paid to the persons from whose custody the`
  line `assets were seized.`
  line `( 4 ) ( a ) The Central Government shall pay simple interest at the rate of 3 [one-half per cent. for every`
  line `month or part of a month] on the amount by which the aggregate amount of money seized under section`
  line `132 or requisitioned under section 132A, as reduced by the amount of money, if any, released under the`
  line `first proviso to clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ), and of the proceeds, if any, of the assets sold towards the`
  line `discharge of the existing liability referred to in clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ), exceeds the aggregate of the`
  line `amount required to meet the liabilities referred to in clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of this section.`
  line `( b ) Such interest shall run from the date immediately following the expiry of the period of one`
  line `hundred and twenty days from the date on which the last of the authorisations for search under section`
  line `132 or requisition under section 132A was executed to the date of completion of the assessment`
  line `4 [under section 153A or under Chapter XIVB].`
  line `5 [ Explanation 1.] — In this section, —`
  line `( i ) “block period” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( a) of section 158B;`
  line `( ii ) “execution of an authorisation for search or requisition” shall have the same meaning as`
  line `assigned to it in Explanation 2 to section 158BE.]`
  line `6 [ Explanation 2. —For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the “existing liability” does`
  line `not include advance tax payable in accordance with the provisions of Part C of Chapter XVII.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 43, for “six per cent. per annum” (w.e.f. 1 -4- 2008). Earlier “six” was substituted for “eight”`
  line `by Act 54 of 2003, s. 6 (w.e.f. 8-9-2003).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 60, for “under Chapter XIV- B” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2003).`
  line `5. The Explanation renumbered as Explanation 1 thereof by Act 17 of 2013, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
  line `6. Ins. by s. 34, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
