obj_root_law_sections_551_content:
  string
  line 551
  line `133. Power to call for information. — The 1 [Assessing Officer], the 2 [Deputy Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals)], 3 [the 4 [Joint Commissioner] or the Commissioner (Appeals)] may, for the purposes of this`
  line `Act, —`
  line `( 1 ) require any firm to furnish him with a return of the names and addresses of the partners of the`
  line `firm and their respective shares;`
  line `( 2 ) require any Hindu undivided family to furnish him with a return of the names and addresses`
  line `of the manager and the members of the family;`
  line `( 3 ) require any person whom he has reason to believe to be a trustee, guardian or agent, to furnish`
  line `him with a return of the names of the persons for or of whom he is trustee, guardian or agent, and of`
  line `their addresses;`
  line `( 4 ) require any assessee to furnish a statement of the names and addresses of all persons to whom`
  line `he has paid in any previous year rent, interest, commission, royalty or brokerage, or any annuity, not`
  line `being any annuity taxable under the head “Salaries” amoun ting to more than 5 [one thousand rupees,`
  line `or such higher amount as may be prescribed], together with particulars of all such payments made;`
  line `( 5 ) require any dealer, broker or agent or any person concerned in the management of a stock or`
  line `commodity exchange to furnish a statement of the names and addresses of all persons to whom he or`
  line `the exchange has paid any sum in connection with the transfer, whether by way of sale, exchange or`
  line `otherwise, of assets, or on whose behalf or from whom he or the exchange has received any such`
  line `sum, together with particulars of all such payments and receipts;`
  line `( 6 ) require any person, including a banking company or any officer thereof, to furnish`
  line `information in relation to such points or matters, or to furnish statements of accounts and affairs`
  line `verified in the manner specified by the 1 [Assessing Officer], the 6 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)],`
  line `3 [the 7 [Joint Commissioner] or the Commissioner (Appeals)], giving information in relation to such`
  line `points or matters as, in the opinion of the 1 [Assessing Officer], the 6 [Deputy Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals)], 3 [the 7 [Joint Commissioner] or the Commissioner (Appeals)], will be useful for, or`
  line `relevant to, any 8 [enquiry or] proceeding under this Act:`
  line `9 [Provided that the powers referred to in clause ( 6 ), may also be exercised by the 10 [Principal`
  line `Director General or Director General], the 11 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner],`
  line `the 12 [Principal Director or Director] 13 [or the Principal Commissioner or Commissioner or the Joint`
  line `Director or Deputy Director or Assistant Director]:`
  line `8 [Provided further that the power in respect of an inquiry, in a case where no proceeding is`
  line `pending, shall not be exercised by any income-tax authority below the rank of 12 [Principal Director or`
  line `Director] or 13 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner 14 [, other than the Joint Director or Deputy`
  line `Director or Assistant Director,]] without the prior approval of the 12 [Principal Director or Director] or,`
  line `as the case may be, the 13 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]:]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988)`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule, for “or the Inspecting Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 10 -7-1978).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 3, for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1-10-1998). Earlier Substituted by 4 of 1988, s. 2`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 39, for “four hundred rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. Subs. by 21 of 1998, s. 3, for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10- 1998). Earlier Substituted as “Deputy Commissioner”`
  line `for “Inspecting Assistant Commissioner” by 4 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-7-1995).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 39 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Director General” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `11. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Chief Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `12. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Director” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `13. S ubs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 52, for “and the Principal Commissioner or Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `14. Ins. by s. 52, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
