obj_root_law_sections_552_content:
  string
  line 552
  line `1 [Provided also that for the purposes of an agreement referred to in section 90 or section 90A, an`
  line `income-tax authority notified under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 131 may exercise all the powers conferred`
  line `under this section, notwithstanding that no proceedings are pending before it or any other income-tax`
  line authority.]
  line `2 [ 133A. Power of survey. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this`
  line `Act, an income-tax authority may enter —`
  line `( a ) any place within the limits of the area assigned to him, or`
  line `( b ) any place occupied by any person in respect of whom he exercises jurisdiction, 3 [or]`
  line `3 [( c ) any place in respect of which he is authorised for the purposes of this section by such`
  line `income-tax authority, who is assigned the area within which such place is situated or who exercises`
  line `jurisdiction in respect of any person occupying such place,]`
  line `4 [at which a business or profession or an activity for charitable purpose is carried on, whether such place`
  line `be the principal place or not of such business or profession or of such activity for charitable purpose, and`
  line `require any proprietor, trustee, employee or any other person who may at that time and place be attending`
  line `in any manner to, or helping in, the carrying on of such business or profession or such activity for`
  line `charitable purpose — ]`
  line `( i ) to afford him the necessary facility to inspect such books of account or other documents as he`
  line `may require and which may be available at such place,`
  line `( ii ) to afford him the necessary facility to check or verify the cash, stock or other valuable article`
  line `or thing which may be found therein, and`
  line `( iii ) to furnish such information as he may require as to any matter which may be useful for, or`
  line `relevant to, any proceeding under this Act.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, a place where a business or profession 5 [or`
  line `activity for charitable purpose] is carried on shall also include any other place, whether any business or`
  line `profession 5 [or activity for charitable purpose] is carried on therein or not, in which the person carrying on`
  line `the business or profession 5 [or activity for charitable purpose] states that any of his books of account or`
  line `other documents or any part of his cash or stock or other valuable article or thing relating to his business`
  line `or profession 5 [or activity for charitable purpose] are or is kept.`
  line `( 2 ) An income-tax authority may enter any place of business or profession referred to in sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) only during the hours at which such place is open for the conduct of business or profession and, in the`
  line `case of any other place, only after sunrise and before sunset.`
  line `6 [( 2A ) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ), an income-tax authority acting under`
  line `this sub-section may for the purpose of verifying that tax has been deducted or collected at source in`
  line `accordance with the provisions under sub-heading B of Chapter XVII or under sub-heading BB of`
  line `Chapter XVII, as the case may be, enter, after sunrise and before sunset, any office, or any other place`
  line `where business or profession is carried on, within the limits of the area assigned to him, or any place in`
  line `respect of which he is authorised for the purposes of this section by such income-tax authority who is`
  line `assigned the area within which such place is situated, where books of account or documents are kept and`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-6-2011).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 37, for section 133A (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1-7-1995).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 53, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 53, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
