obj_root_law_sections_553_content:
  string
  line 553
  line `require the deductor or the collector or any other person who may at that time and place be attending in`
  line `any manner to such work, —`
  line `( i ) to afford him the necessary facility to inspect such books of account or other documents as he`
  line `may require and which may be available at such place, and`
  line `( ii ) to furnish such information as he may require in relation to such matter.]`
  line `( 3 ) An income-tax authority acting under this section may, —`
  line `( i ) if he so deems necessary, place marks of identification on the books of account or other`
  line `documents inspected by him and make or cause to be made extracts or copies therefrom,`
  line `1 [( ia ) impound and retain in his custody for such period as he thinks fit any books of account or`
  line `other documents inspected by him:`
  line `Provided that such income-tax authority shall not —`
  line `( a ) impound any books of account or other documents except after recording his reasons for`
  line `so doing; or`
  line `2 [( b ) retain in his custody any such books of account or other documents for a period`
  line `exceeding fifteen days (exclusive of holidays) without obtaining the approval of the Principal`
  line `Chief Commissioner or the Chief Commissioner or the Principal Director General or the Director`
  line `General or the Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner or the Principal Director or the`
  line `Director therefor, as the case may be,]]`
  line `( ii ) make an inventory of any cash, stock or other valuable article or thing checked or verified by`
  line him,
  line `( iii ) record the statement of any person which may be useful for, or relevant to, any proceeding`
  line `under this Act:`
  line `3 [Provided that no action under clause ( ia ) or clause ( ii ) shall be taken by an income-tax authority`
  line `acting under sub-section ( 2A ).]`
  line `( 4 ) An income-tax authority acting under this section shall, on no account, remove or cause to be`
  line `removed from the place wherein he has entered, 4 *** any cash, stock or other valuable article or thing.`
  line `( 5 ) Where, having regard to the nature and scale of expenditure incurred by an assessee, in connection`
  line `with any function, ceremony or event, the income-tax authority is of the opinion that it is necessary or`
  line `expedient so to do, he may, at any time after such function, ceremony or event, require the assessee by`
  line `whom such expenditure has been incurred or any person who, in the opinion of the income-tax authority,`
  line `is likely to possess information as respects the expenditure incurred, to furnish such information as he`
  line `may require as to any matter which may be useful for, or relevant to, any proceeding under this Act and`
  line `may have the statements of the assessee or any other person recorded and any statement so recorded may`
  line `thereafter be used in evidence in any proceeding under this Act.`
  line `( 6 ) If a person under this section is required to afford facility to the income-tax authority to inspect`
  line `books of account or other documents or to check or verify any cash, stock or other valuable article or`
  line `thing or to furnish any information or to have his statement recorded either refuses or evades to do so, the`
  line `income-tax authority shall have all the powers under 5 [sub-section ( 1 ) of section 131] for enforcing`
  line `compliance with the requirement made:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 58 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 47, ibid., for clause ( ia ) (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 47, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `4. The words “any books of account or other documents or” omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 58 (w.e.f. 1 -6-2002).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 126, for “sub -sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) of section 131 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_553_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_554:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-554
