  title `Page 554`
  content obj_root_law_sections_554_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_554_footnotes
  sourcePage 554
obj_root_law_sections_554_content:
  string
  line 554
  line `1 [Provided that no action under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be taken by an Assistant Director or a Deputy`
  line `Director or an Assessing Officer or a Tax Recovery Officer or an Inspector of Income-tax without`
  line `obtaining the approval of the Joint Director or the Joint Commissioner, as the case may be.]`
  line `Explanation. — In this section, —`
  line `2 [( a ) “income - tax authority” means a 3 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner], a Joint`
  line `Commissioner, a 4 [Principal Director or Director], a Joint Director, an Assistant Director or a Deputy`
  line `Director or an Assessing Officer, or a Tax Recovery Officer, and for the purposes of clause (i) of`
  line `sub-section (1), clause (i) of sub-section (3) and sub-section (5), includes an Inspector of Income-tax;]`
  line `( b ) “proceeding” means any proceeding under this Act in respect of any year which may be`
  line `pending on the date on which the powers under this section are exercised or which may have been`
  line `completed on or before such date and includes also all proceedings under this Act which may be`
  line `commenced after such date in respect of any year.`
  line `5 [ 133B.Power to collect certain information. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other`
  line `provision of this Act, an income-tax authority may, for the purpose of collecting any information which`
  line `may be useful for, or relevant to, the purposes of this Act, enter —`
  line `( a ) any building or place within the limits of the area assigned to such authority; or`
  line `( b ) any building or place occupied by any person in respect of whom he exercises jurisdiction,`
  line `at which a business or profession is carried on, whether such place be the principal place or not of such`
  line `business or profession, and require any proprietor, employee or any other person who may at that time`
  line `and place be attending in any manner to, or helping in, the carrying on of such business or profession to`
  line `furnish such information as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 2 ) An income-tax authority may enter any place of business or profession referred to in sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) only during the hours at which such place is open for the conduct of business or profession.`
  line `( 3 ) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that an income-tax authority acting under this`
  line `section shall, on no account, remove or cause to be removed from the building or place wherein he has`
  line `entered, any books of account or other documents or any cash, stock or other valuable article or thing.`
  line `Explanation. —In this section, “income - tax authority” means a 6 [Joint Commissioner], an 7 [Assistant`
  line `Director]or 8 [Deputy Director] or an 9 [Assessing Officer], and includes an Inspector of Income-tax who`
  line `has been authorised by the 9 [Assessing Officer] to exercise the powers conferred under this section in`
  line `relation to the area in respect of which the 9 [Assessing Officer] exercises jurisdiction or part thereof.]`
  line `10 [ 133C.Power to call for information by prescribed income-tax authority. — 11 [ ( 1 ) ] The`
  line `prescribed income-tax authority may, for the purposes of verification of information in its possession`
  line `relating to any person, issue a notice to such person requiring him, on or before a date to be specified`
  line `therein, to furnish information or documents verified in the manner specified therein, which may be`
  line `useful for, or relevant to, any inquiry or proceeding under this Act.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 61 (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line `2. Subs.by s. 61, ibid., for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Director” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 23 of 1986, s. 27 (w.e.f. 13-5-1986).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 3, for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10- 1998). Earlier “Deputy Commissioner” was`
  line `substituted for “Inspecting Assistant Commissioner” by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Assistant Director of Inspection” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for “Deputy Director of Inspection” ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `9. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 48 (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `11. Section 133C renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 28 of 2016, s. 66 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
