obj_root_law_sections_555_content:
  string
  line 555
  line `1 [ ( 2 ) Where any information or document has been received in response to a notice issued under sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ), the prescribed income-tax authority may process such information or document and make`
  line `available the outcome of such processing to the Assessing Officer. ]`
  line `2 [( 3 ) The Board may make a scheme for centralized issuance of notice and for processing of`
  line `information or documents and making available the outcome of the processing to the Assessing Officer.]`
  line `Explanation. —In this section, the term “proceeding” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause`
  line `( b ) of the Explanation to section 133A.]`
  line `134. Power to inspect registers of companies. — The 3 [Assessing Officer], the 4 [Deputy`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals)], 5 [the 6 [Joint Commissioner] or the Commissioner (Appeals)], or any person`
  line `subordinate to him authorised in writing in this behalf by the 3 [Assessing Officer], the 4 [Deputy`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals)], 5 [the 6 [Joint Commissioner] or the Commissioner (Appeals)], may inspect, and`
  line `if necessary, take copies, or cause copies to be taken, of any register of the members, debenture holders or`
  line `mortgagees of any company or of any entry in such register.`
  line `135. Power of 7 [ 8 [ Principal Director General or Director General]] or 9 [Principal Director`
  line `orDirector], 10 [ 11 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner]] or 12 [Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner] and 13 [Joint Commissioner]. — The 8 [Principal Director General or`
  line `Director General] or 9 [Principal Director or Director], the 10 [ 11 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner]] or 12 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] and the 13 [Joint Commissioner] shall be`
  line `competent to make any enquiry under this Act, and for this purpose shall have all the powers that`
  line `an 3 [Assessing Officer] has under this Act in relation to the making of enquiries.`
  line `136. Proceedings before income-tax authorities to be judicial proceedings. — Any proceeding`
  line `under this Act before an income-tax authority shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of sections 193 and 228 and for the purposes of section 196 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of`
  line `1860) 14 [and every income-tax authority shall be deemed to be a Civil Court for the purposes of section`
  line `195, but not for the purposes of Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).]`
  line `D. Disclosure of information`
  line `[137. Disclosure of information prohibited.] Omitted by the Finance Act, 1964 (5 of 1964), s. 32`
  line `( w.e.f. 1-4-1964).`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 66 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 54 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 10, for “or the Inspecting Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 10 -7-1978).Earlier Subs. by Act 21`
  line `of 1998, s. 3, for “Deputy commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10- 1998). Which was earlier subs. by 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Inspecting`
  line `Assistant Commiss ioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 3, for “Deputy commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10- 1998). Earlier “Deputy commissioner” was`
  line `substituted for “Inspecting Assistant Commissioner” by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 4 of 1 988, s. 2, for “Director of Inspection” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Director General” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `9. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Director” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013)`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 3, for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10- 1998). Earlier “Deputy Commissioner” was`
  line `substituted for “Inspecting Assistant Commissioner” by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014,s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `12. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `13. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 3, for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `14. Ins. by Act 32 of 1985, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
