obj_root_law_sections_556_content:
  string
  line 556
  line `1 [ 138. Disclosure of information respecting assessees. — 2 [( 1 )( a ) The Board or any other income-tax`
  line `authority specified by it by a general or special order in this behalf may furnish or cause to be furnished`
  line `to —`
  line `( i ) any officer, authority or body performing any functions under any law relating to the`
  line `imposition of any tax, duty or cess, or to dealings in foreign exchange as defined in 3 [clause ( n ) of`
  line `section 2 of the Foreign Exchange Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999)]; or`
  line `( ii ) such officer, authority or body performing functions under any other law as the Central`
  line `Government may, if in its opinion it is necessary so to do in the public interest, specify by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette in this behalf,`
  line `any such information 4 [received or obtained by any income-tax authority in the performance of his`
  line `functions under this Act], as may, in the opinion of the Board or other income-tax authority, be necessary`
  line `for the purpose of enabling the officer, authority or body to perform his or its functions under that law.`
  line `(b) Where a person makes an application to the 5 [ 6 [PrincipalChief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner] or 7 [PrincipalCommissioner or Commissioner]] in the prescribed form for any`
  line `information relating to any assessee 8 [received or obtained by any income-tax authority in the performance`
  line `of his functions under this Act], the 5 [ 6 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or`
  line `7 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] may, if he is satisfied that it is in the public interest so to do,`
  line `furnish or cause to be furnished the information asked for 9 *** and his decision in this behalf shall be`
  line `final and shall not be called in question in any court of law.]`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ) or any other law for the time being in`
  line `force, the Central Government may, having regard to the practices and usages customary or any other`
  line `relevant factors, by order notified in the Official Gazette, direct that no information or document shall be`
  line `furnished or produced by a public servant in respect of such matters relating to such class of assessees or`
  line `except to such authorities as may be specified in the order.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 1964, s. 33, for section 138 (w.e.f. 1-4-1964).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 28, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1967).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 35, for “section 2 ( d ) of the Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1947 (7 of 1947)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-`
  line `2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 41, for “relating to any assessee in respect of any assessment made under this Act or under the`
  line `Indian Income- tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 41, for “in respect of any assessment made under this Act or the Indian Income -tax`
  line `Act, 1922 (11 of 1922), on or after the 1st day of April, 1960” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `9. The words “in respect of that assessment only” omitted by s. 41, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
