obj_root_law_sections_559_content:
  string
  line 559
  line `Explanation 3. — For the purposes of this sub- section, the expression “travel to any foreign country”`
  line `does not include travel to the neighbouring countries or to such places of pilgrimage as the Board may`
  line `specify in this behalf by notification in the Official Gazette.]`
  line `1 [ Explanation 4. —For the purposes of this section “beneficial owner” in respect of an asset means an`
  line `individual who has provided, directly or indirectly, consideration for the asset for the immediate or future`
  line `benefit, direct or indirect, of himself or any other person.`
  line `Explanation 5. — For the purposes of this section “beneficiary” in respect of an asset means an`
  line `individual who derives benefit from the asset during the previous year and the consideration for such`
  line `asset has been provided by any person other than such beneficiary.]`
  line `2 [( 1A ) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ), any person, being an individual who is`
  line `in receipt of income chargeable under the head “Salaries” may, at his option, furnish a return of his`
  line `income for any previous year to his employer, in accordance with such scheme as may be specified by the`
  line `Board in this behalf, by notification in the Official Gazette, and subject to such conditions as may be`
  line `specified therein, and such employer shall furnish all returns of income received by him on or before the`
  line `due date, in such form (including on a floppy, diskette, magnetic cartridge tape, CD-ROM or any other`
  line `computer readable media) and manner as may be specified in that scheme, and in such case, any`
  line `employee who has filed a return of his income to his employer shall be deemed to have furnisheda return`
  line `of income under sub-section ( 1 ), and the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly.]`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 [( 1B ) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ), any person, being a company or being a`
  line `person other than a company, required to furnish a return of income under sub-section ( 1 ), may, at his`
  line `option, on or before the due date, furnish a return of his income for any previous year in accordance with`
  line `such scheme as may be specified by the Board in this behalf by notification in the Official Gazette and`
  line `subject to such conditions as may be specified therein, in such form (including on a floppy, diskette,`
  line `magnetic cartridge tape, CD-ROM or any other computer readable media) and in the manner as may be`
  line `specified in that scheme, and in such case, the return of income furnished under such scheme shall be`
  line `deemed to be a return furnished under sub-section ( 1 ), and the provisions of this Act shall apply`
  line accordingly.]
  line `5 [( 1C ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, exempt any class or classes of persons from the requirement of`
  line `furnishing a return of income having regard to such conditions as may be specified in that notification.]`
  line `6 * * * * *`
  line `( 3 ) If any person who 7 *** has sustained a loss in any previous year under the head “Profits and gains`
  line `of business or profes sion” or under the head “Capital gains” and claims that the loss or any part thereof`
  line `should be carried forward under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 72, or sub-section ( 2 ) of section 73, 8 [or sub-`
  line `section ( 2 ) of section 73A] or 9 [sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 3 ) of section 74], 10 [or sub-section ( 3 )`
  line `of section 74A], he may furnish, within the time allowed under sub-section ( 1 ), 11 *** a return of loss in`
  line `the prescribed form and verified in the prescribed manner and containing such other particulars as may be`
  line `prescribed, and all the provisions of this Act shall apply as if it were a return under sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 59 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).Earlier sub-section ( 1A ) was amended by 13 of 1963, s. 8 (w.e.f. 14-1962).`
  line `Earlier amended by 19 of 1970, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `3. Explanation omitted by Act 67 of 1984, s. 25 (w.ef. 1-4-1985).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 62 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-6-2011).`
  line `6. Sub-section ( 2 ) omittedby Act 4 of 1988, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `7. The words “has not been served with a notice under sub -section ( 2 )” omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 67 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 74, for “sub -section ( 1 ) of section 74” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 20 of 1974, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-1975).`
  line `11. The words “or by the thirty -first day of July of the assessment year relevant to the previous year during which the loss`
  line `was sustained” by Act 4 of 1988, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
