obj_root_law_sections_560_content:
  string
  line 560
  line `1 [ 2 [( 4 ) Anyperson who has not furnished a return within the time allowed to him under sub-section`
  line `( 1 ), may furnish the return for any previous year at any time before the end of the relevant assessment`
  line `year or before the completion of the assessment, whichever is earlier.]`
  line `3 [( 4A ) Every person in receipt of income derived from property held under trust or other legal`
  line `obligation wholly for charitable or religious purposes or in part only for such purposes, or of income`
  line `being voluntary contributions referred to in sub-clause ( iia ) of clause ( 24 ) of section 2, shall, if the total`
  line `income in respect of which he is assessable as a representative assessee (the total income for this purpose`
  line `being computed under this Act without giving effect to the provisions of sections 11 and 12) exceeds the`
  line `maximum amount which is not chargeable to income-tax, furnish a return of such income of the previous`
  line `year in the prescribed form and verified in the prescribed manner and setting forth such other particulars`
  line `as may be prescribed and all the provisions of this Act shall, so far as may be, apply as if it were a return`
  line `required to be furnished under sub-section ( 1 ).]]`
  line `4 [( 4B ) The chief executive officer (whether such chief executive officer is known as Secretary or by`
  line `any other designation) of every political party shall, if the total income in respect of which the political`
  line `party is assessable (the total income for this purpose being computed under this Act without giving effect`
  line `to the provisions of section 13A) exceeds the maximum amount which is not chargeable to income-tax,`
  line `furnish a return of such income of the previous year in the prescribed form and verified in the prescribed`
  line `manner and setting forth such other particulars as may be prescribed and all the provisions of this Act,`
  line `shall, so far as may be, apply as if it were a return required to be furnished under sub-section ( 1 ).]`
  line `5 [( 4C ) Every —`
  line `( a ) 6 [researchassociation] referred to in clause ( 21 ) of section 10;`
  line `( b ) news agency referred to in clause ( 22B ) of section 10;`
  line `( c ) association or institution referred to in clause ( 23A ) of section 10;`
  line `7 [( ca )person referred to in clause ( 23AAA ) of section 10;]`
  line `( d ) institution referred to in clause ( 23B ) of section 10;`
  line `( e ) fund or institution referred to in sub-clause ( iv ) or trust or institution referred to in sub-clause`
  line `( v ) or any university or other educational institution referred to in 8 [sub-clause ( iiiab ) or] 9 [sub-clause`
  line `( iiiad ) or sub-clause ( vi )] or any hospital or other medical institution referred to in 8 [sub-clause ( iiiac )`
  line `or] 10 [sub-clause ( iiiae ) or sub-clause ( via )] of clause ( 23C ) of section 10;`
  line `11 [( ea ) Mutual Fund referred to in clause ( 23D ) of section 10;`
  line `( eb ) securitisation trust referred to in clause ( 23DA ) of section 10;`
  line `7 [( eba ) InvestorProtection Fund referred to in clause ( 23EC ) or clause ( 23ED ) of section 10;`
  line `( ebb ) Core Settlement Guarantee Fund referred to in clause ( 23EE ) of section 10;]`
  line `( ec ) venture capital company or venture capital fund referred to in clause ( 23FB ) of section 10;]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 42, for sub-sections ( 4 ) and ( 4a ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 67, for sub-section ( 4 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2017). Earlier sub-section ( 4 ) was substituted by Act 4 of`
  line `1988, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 20, for sub-section ( 4A ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Original sub-section ( 4A ) was inserted by Act 19 of`
  line `1970, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971) and substituted by Act 16 of 1972, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 29 of 1978, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1979).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 59 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 32, for “scientific research association” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2011).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 55 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 12, for “sub -clause ( vi )” (w.r.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `10. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for “sub -clause ( via )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `11. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 49 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
