obj_root_law_sections_562_content:
  string
  line 562
  line `1 [( 6 ) The prescribed form of the returns referred to 2 [in sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 3 ) of this section, and in`
  line `clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142] shall, in such cases as may be prescribed, require the assessee`
  line `to furnish the particulars of income exempt from tax, 3 [assets of the prescribed nature and 4 [value, held by`
  line `him as a beneficial owner or otherwise in which he is a beneficiary], his bank account and credit card held`
  line `by him], expenditure exceeding the prescribed limits incurred by him under prescribed heads and such`
  line `other out-goings as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 6A ) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section ( 6 ), the prescribed form of the returns referred`
  line `to 5 [in 6 *** this section, and in clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142]shall, in the case of an assessee`
  line `engaged in any business or profession, also require him to furnish 7 [the report of any audit 8 [referred to`
  line `in section 44AB,or, where the report has been furnished prior to the furnishing of the return, a copy of`
  line `such report together with proof of furnishing the report]], the particulars of the location and style of the`
  line `principal place where he carries on the business or profession and all the branches thereof, the names and`
  line `addresses of his partners, if any, in such business or profession and, if he is a member of an association or`
  line `body of individuals, the names of the other members of the association or the body of individuals and the`
  line `extent of the share of the assessee and the shares of all such partners or the members, as the case may be,`
  line `in the profits of the business or profession and any branches thereof.]`
  line `9 * * * * *`
  line `10 [( 8 ) ( a ) 11 [Where the return under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-section ( 4 ) for an`
  line `assessment year is furnished after the specified date, or is not furnished, then [whether or not the`
  line `12 [Assessing Officer] has extended the date for furnishing the return under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section`
  line `( 2 )], the assessee shall be liable to pay simple interest at 13 [fifteen per cent.] per annum, reckoned from`
  line `the day immediately following the specified date to the date of the furnishing of the return or, where no`
  line `return has been furnished, the date of completion of the assessment under section 144, on the amount of`
  line `the tax payable on the total income as determined on regular assessment, as reduced by the advance tax, if`
  line `any, paid, and any tax deducted at source:`
  line `Provided that the 12 [Assessing Officer] may, in such cases and under such circumstances as may be`
  line `prescribed, reduce or waive the interest payable by any assessee under this sub-section.`
  line `Explanation 1. — For the purposes of this sub- section, “specified date”, in relation to a return for an`
  line `assessment year, means, —`
  line `( a ) in the case of every assessee whose total income, or the total income of any person in respect`
  line `of which he is assessable under this Act, includes any income from business or profession, the date of`
  line `the expiry of four months from the end of the previous year or where there is more than one previous`
  line `year, from the end of the previous year which expired last before the commencement of the`
  line `assessment year or the 30th day of June of the assessment year, whichever is later;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 38, for sub-section ( 6 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 42, for “in sub -sections ( 1 ), ( 2 ) and ( 3 )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 35, for “assets of the prescribed nature, value and belonging to him” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2016).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 62, for “and value and belonging to him” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1999).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 42, for “in sub -sections ( 1 ), ( 2 ) and ( 3 )”(w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `6. The words “sub -sections ( 1 ) and ( 3 ) of” omitted by Act 22 of 1995, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1 -7-1995).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 29, for “obtained under section 44AB” (w.e.f. 1 -7-1995).`
  line `9. Sub-section ( 7 ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 26, for sub-section ( 8 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1971). Earlier sub-section ( 8 ) was inserted by Act 13 of`
  line `1963, s. 8 (w.e.f. 28-4-1963).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 26, for the portion beginning with “Where the return” and ending with “under this sub -`
  line `section” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1972).`
  line `12. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `13. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 25, for “twelve per cent.” (w.e. f. 1-10-1984).`
