obj_root_law_sections_563_content:
  string
  line 563
  line `( b ) in the case of every other assessee, the 30th day of June of the assessment year.]`
  line `1 [ Explanation 2. — Where, in relation to an assessment year, an assessment is made for the first time`
  line `under section 147, the assessment so made shall be regarded as a regular assessment for the purposes of`
  line `this sub-section.]`
  line `2 [( b ) Where as a result of an order under section 147 or section 154 or section 155 or section`
  line `250 or section 254 or section 260 or section 262 or section 263 or section 264 3 [or an order of the`
  line `Settlement Commission under sub-section (4) of section 245D], the amount of tax on which interest was`
  line `payable under this sub-section has been increased or reduced, as the case may be, the interest shall be`
  line `increased or reduced accordingly, and —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the interest is increased, the 4 [Assessing Officer] shall serve on the assessee, a`
  line `notice of demand in the prescribed form specifying the sum payable, and such notice of demand shall`
  line `be deemed to be a notice under section 156 and the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly;`
  line `( ii ) in a case where the interest is reduced, the excess interest paid, if any, shall be refunded.]]`
  line `5 [( c ) The provisions of this sub-section shall apply in respect of the assessment for the assessment`
  line `year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1988, or any earlier assessment year, and references therein to`
  line `the other provisions of this Act shall be construed as references to the said provisions as they were`
  line `applicable to the relevant assessment year.]`
  line `6 [( 9 ) Where the 4 [Assessing Officer] considers that the return of income furnished by the assessee is`
  line `defective, he may intimate the defect to the assessee and give him an opportunity to rectify the defect`
  line `within a period of fifteen days from the date of such intimation or within such further period which, on an`
  line `application made in this behalf, the 4 [Assessing Officer] may, in his discretion, allow; and if the defect is`
  line `not rectified within the said period of fifteen days or, as the case may be, the further period so allowed,`
  line `then, notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, the return shall be treated as`
  line `an invalid return and the provisions of this Act shall apply as if the assessee had failed to furnish the`
  line `return:`
  line `Provided that where the assessee rectifies the defect after the expiry of the said period of fifteen days`
  line `or the further period allowed, but before the assessment is made, the 4 [Assessing Officer] may condone`
  line `the delay and treat the return as a valid return.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, a return of income shall be regarded as defective`
  line `unless all the following conditions are fulfilled, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the annexures, statements and columns in the return of income relating to computation of`
  line `income chargeable under each head of income, computation of gross total income and total income`
  line `have been duly filled in;`
  line `7 * * * * *`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 25, for Explanation2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1985). Earlier the Explanation was renumbered as`
  line `Explanation2 thereof by Act 16 of 1972, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 25, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 126 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 2, ibid.,for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 42, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-9-1980).`
  line `7. Clause ( aa ) omitted by Act 28 of 2016, s. 67 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017). Earlier clause ( aa ) omitted by Act 17 of 2013, s. 36`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
