obj_root_law_sections_564_content:
  string
  line 564
  line `( b ) the return is accompanied by a statement showing the computation of the tax payable on the`
  line `basis of the return;`
  line `1 [( bb ) the return is accompanied by the report of the audit referred to in section 44AB, or, where`
  line `the report has been furnished prior to the furnishing of the return, by a copy of such report together`
  line `with proof of furnishing the report;]`
  line `( c ) the return is accompanied by proof of —`
  line `( i ) the tax, if any, claimed to have been 2 [deducted or collected at source] 3 *** and the`
  line `advance tax and tax on self-assessment, if any, claimed to have been paid:`
  line `4 [Provided that where the return is not accompanied by proof of the tax, if any, 5 [claimed to`
  line `have been deducted or collected at source], the return of income shall not be regarded as defective`
  line `if —`
  line `6 [( a ) a certificate for tax deducted or collected was not furnished under section`
  line `203 or section 206C to the person furnishing his return of income;]`
  line `( b ) such certificate is produced within a period of two years specified under sub-section`
  line `( 14 ) of section 155;]`
  line `( ii ) the amount of compulsory deposit, if any, claimed to have been made under the`
  line `Compulsory Deposit Scheme (Income-tax Payers) Act, 1974 (38 of 1974);`
  line `( d ) where regular books of account are maintained by the assessee, the return is accompanied by`
  line `copies of —`
  line `( i ) manufacturing account, trading account, profit and loss account or, as the case may be,`
  line `income and expenditure account or any other similar account and balance sheet;`
  line `( ii ) in the case of a proprietary business or profession, the personal account of the proprietor;`
  line `in the case of a firm, association of persons or body of individuals, personal accounts of the`
  line `partners or members; and in the case of a partner or member of a firm, association of persons or`
  line `body of individuals, also his personal account in the firm, association of persons or body of`
  line individuals;
  line `( e ) where the accounts of the assessee have been audited, the return is accompanied by copies of`
  line `the audited profit and loss account and balance sheet and the 7 [auditor’s report and, where an audit of`
  line `cost accounts of the assessee has been conducted under section 233B of the Companies Act, 1956 (1`
  line `of 1956), also the report under that section];`
  line `( f ) where regular books of account are not maintained by the assessee, the return is accompanied`
  line `by a statement indicating the amounts of turnover or, as the case may be, gross receipts, gross profit,`
  line `expenses and net profit of the business or profession and the basis on which such amounts have been`
  line `computed, and also disclosing the amounts of total sundry debtors, sundry creditors, stock-in-trade`
  line `and cash balance as at the end of the previous year.]`
  line `8 * * * * *`
  line `9 * * * * *`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 29, for clause ( bb ) (w.e.f. 1-7-1995). Earlier clause ( bb ) was inserted by Act 26 of 1988, s. 35`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 31, for “deducted at source” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2007).`
  line `3. The words “before the 1st day of April, 2008” omitted by Act 18 of 2008, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1 -4-2008).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 59 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 31, for “claimed to have been deducted at source” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2007).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 32 of 1985, s. 29, for “auditor’s report” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1985).`
  line `8. The proviso omitted by Act 22 of 2007, s. 44 (w.e.f. 1-6-2006). Earlier the proviso inserted by Act 21 of 2006,`
  line `s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-6-2006).`
  line `9. Sub-section ( 10 ) omitted by Act 49 of 1991, s. 44 (w.e.f. -4-1991).`
