  content obj_root_law_sections_565_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_565_footnotes
  sourcePage 565
obj_root_law_sections_565_content:
  string
  line 565
  line `1 [139A. Permanent account number. — ( 1 ) Every person, —`
  line `( i ) if his total income or the total income of any other person in respect of which he is assessable`
  line `under this Act during any previous year exceeded the maximum amount which is not chargeable to`
  line `income-tax; or`
  line `( ii ) carrying on any business or profession whose total sales, turnover or gross receipts are or is`
  line `likely to exceed 2 [five lakhrupees] in any previous year; or`
  line `( iii ) who is required to furnish a return of income under 3 [sub-section (4A) of section 139;or`
  line `( iv ) being an employer, who is required to furnish a return of fringe benefits under`
  line `section 115WD,] 4 [or]`
  line `4 [( v ) being a resident, other than an individual, which enters into a financial transaction of an`
  line `amount aggregating to two lakh fifty thousand rupees or more in a financial year; or`
  line `( vi ) who is the managing director, director, partner, trustee, author, founder, karta, chief executive`
  line `officer, principal officer or office bearer of the person referred to in clause ( v ) or any person`
  line `competent to act on behalf of the person referred to in clause ( v ),]`
  line `and who has not been allotted a permanent account number shall, within such time, as may be prescribed,`
  line `apply to the Assessing Officer for the allotment of a permanent account number.`
  line `5 [( 1A ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify, any class or classes of persons by whom tax is payable under`
  line `this Act or any tax or duty is payable under any other law for the time being in force including importers`
  line `and exporters whether any tax is payable by them or not and such persons shall, within such time as`
  line `mentioned in that notification, apply to the Assessing Officer for the allotment of a permanent account`
  line number.]
  line `6 [( 1B ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), the Central Government may, for the`
  line `purpose of collecting any information which may be useful for or relevant to the purposes of this Act, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify, any class or classes of persons who shall apply to the`
  line `Assessing Officer for the allotment of the permanent account number and such persons shall, within such`
  line `time as mentioned in that notification, apply to the Assessing Officer for the allotment of a permanent`
  line `account number.]`
  line `7 [( 2 ) The Assessing Officer, having regard to the nature of the transactions as may be prescribed, may`
  line `also allot a permanent account number, to any other person (whether any tax is payable by him or not), in`
  line `the manner and in accordance with the procedure as may be prescribed.]`
  line `( 3 ) Any person, not falling under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ), may apply to the Assessing`
  line `Officer for the allotment of a permanent account number and, thereupon, the Assessing Officer shall allot`
  line `a permanent account number to such person forthwith.`
  line `( 4 ) For the purpose of allotment of permanent account numbers under the new series, the Board may,`
  line `by notificationin the Official Gazette, specify the date from which the persons referred to in`
  line `sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) and other persons who have been allotted permanent account numbers and`
  line `residing in a place to be specified in such notification, shall, within such time as may be specified, apply`
  line `to the Assessing Officer for the allotment of a permanent account number under the new series and upon`
  line `allotment of such permanent account number to a person, the permanent account number, if any, allotted`
  line `to him earlier shall cease to have effect:`
  line `Provided that the persons to whom permanent account number under the new series has already been`
  line `allotted shall not apply for such number again.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 30, for section 139A (w.e.f. 1-7-1995).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 41, for “fifty thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -8-1998).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 41, for “sub - section (4A) of section 139” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 44 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 58 (w.e.f. 1-6-2000).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-6-2006).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 32, ibid., for sub-section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2006).`
