obj_root_law_sections_566_content:
  string
  line 566
  line `( 5 ) Every person shall —`
  line `( a ) quote such number in all his returns to, or correspondence with, any income-tax authority;`
  line `( b ) quote such number in all challans for the payment of any sum due under this Act;`
  line `( c ) quote such number in all documents pertaining to such transactions as may be prescribedby`
  line `the Board in the interests of the revenue, and entered into by him:`
  line `Provided that the Board may prescribe different dates for different transactions or class of`
  line `transactions or for different class of persons:`
  line `1 [Provided further that a person shall quote General Index Register Number till such time`
  line `Permanent Account Number is allotted to such person;]`
  line `( d ) intimate the Assessing Officer any change in his address or in the name and nature of his`
  line `business on the basis of which the permanent account number was allotted to him.`
  line `2 [( 5A ) Every person receiving any sum or income or amount from which tax has been deducted under`
  line `the provisions of Chapter XVIIB, shall intimate his permanent account number to the person responsible`
  line `for deducting such tax under that Chapter:`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `Provided further that a person referred to in this sub-section shall intimate the General Index Register`
  line `Number till such time permanent account number is allotted to such person.`
  line `( 5B ) Where any sum or income or amount has been paid after deducting tax under Chapter XVIIB,`
  line `every person deducting tax under that Chapter shall quote the permanent account number of the person to`
  line `whom such sum or income or amount has been paid by him —`
  line `( i ) in the statement furnished in accordance with the provisions of sub-section ( 2C ) of`
  line `section 192;`
  line `( ii ) in all certificates furnished in accordance with the provisions of section 203;`
  line `( iii ) in all returns prepared and delivered or caused to be delivered in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of section 206 to any income-tax authority;`
  line `4 [( iv ) in all 5 *** statements prepared and delivered or caused to be delivered in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of sub-section ( 3 ) of section 200:]`
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify`
  line `different dates from which the provisions of this sub-section shall apply in respect of any class or`
  line `classes of persons:`
  line `Provided further that nothing contained in sub-sections ( 5A ) and ( 5B ) shall apply in case of a`
  line `person whose total income is not chargeable to income-tax or who is not required to obtain permanent`
  line `account number under any provision of this Act if such person furnishes to the person responsible for`
  line `deducting tax, a declaration referred to in section 197A in the form and manner prescribed thereunder`
  line `to the effect that the tax on his estimated total income of the previous year in which such income is to`
  line `be included in computing his total income will be nil.`
  line `( 5C ) Every 6 [buyer or licensee or lessee] referred to in section 206C shall intimate his permanent`
  line `account number to the 7 [person responsible for collecting tax] referred to in that section.`
  line `( 5D ) Every 7 [person] collecting tax in accordance with the provisions of section 206C shall quote the`
  line `permanent account number of every 6 [buyer or licensee or lessee] referred to in that section —`
  line `( i ) in all certificates furnished in accordance with the provisions of sub-section ( 5 ) of`
  line `section 206C;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 60 (w.e.f. 1-6-2001).`
  line `3. The first proviso omitted by Act 23 of 2004, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-6-2006).`
  line `5. The word “quarterly” omitted by Act 33 of 2009, s. 53 (w.e.f. 1 -10-2009).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 33, for “buyer” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2004).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 32, for “seller” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2007).`
