obj_root_law_sections_567_content:
  string
  line 567
  line `( ii ) in all returns prepared and delivered or caused to be delivered in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of sub-section ( 5A ) or sub-section ( 5B ) of section 206C to an income-tax authority;]`
  line `1 [( iii ) in all 2 *** statements prepared and delivered or caused to be delivered in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of sub-section ( 3 ) of section 206C.]`
  line `( 6 ) Every person receiving any document relating to a transaction prescribed under clause ( c ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 5 ) shall ensure that the Permanent Account Number 3 [or the General Index Register Number]`
  line `has been duly quoted in the document.`
  line `( 7 ) No person who has already been allotted a permanent account number under the new series shall`
  line `apply, obtain or possess another permanent account number.`
  line `4 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that any person, who has been`
  line `allotted a permanent account number under any clause other than clause ( iv ) of sub-section ( 1 ), shall not`
  line `be required to obtain another permanent account number and the permanent account number already`
  line `allotted to him shall be deemed to be the permanent account number in relation to fringe benefit tax.]`
  line `( 8 ) The Board may make rules providing for —`
  line `( a ) the form and the manner in which an application may be made for the allotment of a`
  line `permanent account number and the particulars which such application shall contain;`
  line `( b ) the categories of transactions in relation to which Permanent Account Numbers 3 [or the`
  line `General Index Register Number] shall be quoted by every person in the documents pertaining to such`
  line transactions;
  line `( c ) the categories of documents pertaining to business or profession in which such numbers shall`
  line `be quoted by every person;`
  line `3 [( d ) class or classes of persons to whom the provisions of this section shall not apply;`
  line `( e ) the form and the manner in which the person who has not been allotted a Permanent Account`
  line `Number or who does not have General Index Register Number shall make his declaration;`
  line `( f ) the manner in which the Permanent Account Number or the General Index Register Number`
  line `shall be quoted in respect of the categories of transactions referred to in clause ( c );`
  line `( g ) the time and the manner in which the transactions referred to in clause ( c ) shall be intimated`
  line `to the prescribed authority.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “Assessing Officer” includes an income -tax authority who is assigned the duty of allotting`
  line `permanent account numbers;`
  line `( b ) “permanent account number” means a number which the Assessing Officer may allot to any`
  line `person for the purpose of identification and includes a permanent account number allotted under the`
  line `new series;`
  line `( c ) “permanent account number under the new series” means a permanent account number having`
  line `ten alphanumeric characters 5 ***;]`
  line `3 [( d ) “General Index Register Number” means a number given by an Assessing Officer to an`
  line `assessee in the General Index Register maintained by him and containing the designation and`
  line `particulars of the ward or circle or range of the Assessing Officer.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-6-2006).`
  line `2. The word “quarterly” omitted by Act 33 of 2009, s. 53 (w.e.f. 1 -10-2009).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `5. The words “and issued in the form of a laminated card” omitted by Act 13 of 2018, s. 44 (w.e.f. 1 -4-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_567_footnotes:
