  title `Page 568`
  content obj_root_law_sections_568_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_568_footnotes
  sourcePage 568
obj_root_law_sections_568_content:
  string
  line 568
  line `1 [ 139AA.Quoting of Aadhaar number. — ( 1 ) Every person who is eligible to obtain Aadhaar`
  line `number shall, on or after the 1st day of July, 2017, quote Aadhaar number —`
  line `( i ) in the application form for allotment of permanent account number;`
  line `( ii ) in the return of income:`
  line `Provided that where the person does not possess the Aadhaar Number, the Enrolment ID of`
  line `Aadhaar application form issued to him at the time of enrolment shall be quoted in the application for`
  line `permanent account number or, as the case may be, in the return of income furnished by him.`
  line `( 2 ) Every person who has been allotted permanent account number as on the 1st day of July, 2017,`
  line `and who is eligible to obtain Aadhaar number, shall intimate his Aadhaar number to such authority in`
  line `such form and manner as may be prescribed, on or before a date to be notified by the Central Government`
  line `in the Official Gazette:`
  line `Provided that in case of failure to intimate the Aadhaar number, the permanent account number`
  line `allotted to the person shall be deemed to be invalid and the other provisions of this Act shall apply, as if`
  line `the person had not applied for allotment of permanent account number.`
  line `( 3 ) The provisions of this section shall not apply to such person or class or classes of persons or any`
  line `State or part of any State, as may be notified by the Central Government in this behalf, in the Official`
  line Gazette.
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, the expressions —`
  line `( i ) “Aadhaar number”, “Enrolment” and “resident” shall have the same meanings respectively`
  line `assigned to them in clauses ( a ), ( m ) and ( v ) of section 2 of the Aadhaar (Targeted Delivery of`
  line `Financial and other Subsidies, Benefits and Services) Act, 2016;`
  line `( ii ) “Enrolment ID” means a 28 digit Enrolment Identification Number issued to a resident at the`
  line `time of enrolment.]`
  line `2 [ 139B. Scheme for submission of returns through Tax Return Preparers. — ( 1 ) For the purpose`
  line `of enabling any specified class or classes of persons in preparing and furnishing returns of income, the`
  line `Board may, without prejudice to the provisions of section 139, frame a Scheme, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, providing that such persons may furnish their returns of income through a Tax Return`
  line `Preparer authorised to act as such under the Scheme.`
  line `( 2 ) Every Tax Return Preparer shall assist the persons furnishing the return of income in such manner`
  line `as may be specified in the Scheme framed under this section and affix his signature on such return.`
  line `( 3 ) For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “Tax Return Preparer” means any individual, [not being a person referred to in clause ( ii ) or`
  line `clause ( iii ) or clause ( iv ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288 or an employee of the “specified class or`
  line `classes of persons”], who has been authorised to act as a Tax Return Preparer under the Scheme`
  line `framed under this section;`
  line `( b ) “specified class or classes of persons” means any person, other than a c ompany or a person,`
  line `whose accounts are required to be audited under section 44AB or under any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, who is required to furnish a return of income under this Act.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 56 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-6-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_568_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_569:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-569
  sectionNo (569)
