  title `Page 569`
  content obj_root_law_sections_569_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_569_footnotes
  sourcePage 569
obj_root_law_sections_569_content:
  string
  line 569
  line `( 4 ) The Scheme framed by the Board under this section may provide for the following, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the manner in which and the period for which the Tax Return Preparers shall be authorised`
  line `under sub-section ( 3 );`
  line `( b ) the educational and other qualifications to be possessed, and the training and other conditions`
  line `required to be fulfilled, by a person to act as a Tax Return Preparer;`
  line `( c ) the code of conduct for the Tax Return Preparers;`
  line `( d ) the duties and obligations of the Tax Return Preparers;`
  line `( e ) the circumstances under which the authorisation given to a Tax Return Preparer may be`
  line withdrawn;
  line `( f ) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, specified by the Scheme for the purposes`
  line `of this section.`
  line `( 5 ) The Scheme framed by the Board under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `framed, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may`
  line `be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the Scheme or both Houses agree that the Scheme should not be framed, the Scheme shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that Scheme.]`
  line `1 [ 139C. Power of Board to dispense with furnishing documents, etc., with return. — ( 1 ) The`
  line `Board may make rules providing for a class or classes of persons who may not be required to furnish`
  line `documents, statements, receipts, certificates, reports of audit or any other documents, which are otherwise`
  line `under any other provisions of this Act, except section 139D, required to be furnished, along with the`
  line `return but on demand to be produced before the Assessing Officer.`
  line `( 2 ) Any rule made under the proviso to sub-section ( 9 ) of section 139 as it stood immediately before`
  line `its omission by the Finance Act, 2007 shall be deemed to have been made under the provisions of this`
  line section.
  line `139D. Filing of return in electronic form. — The Board may make rules providing for —`
  line `( a ) the class or classes of persons who shall be required to furnish the return in electronic form;`
  line `( b ) the form and the manner in which the return in electronic form may be furnished;`
  line `( c ) the documents, statements, receipts, certificates or audited reports which may not be furnished`
  line `along with the return in electronic form but shall be produced before the Assessing Officer on`
  line demand;
  line `( d ) the computer resource or the electronic record to which the return in electronic form may be`
  line transmitted.]
  line `140. Return by whom to be 2 [ verified]. — The return 3 [under section 115WD or section 139] shall be`
  line `4 [verified] —`
  line `5 [( a ) in the case of an individual, —`
  line `( i ) by the individual himself;`
  line `( ii ) where he is absent from India, by the individual himself or by some person duly`
  line `authorised by him in this behalf;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1-6-2006).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 50, for “signed” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2014).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 42, for “under section 139” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 50, for “signed and verified” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2014).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 44, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
