obj_root_law_sections_570_content:
  string
  line 570
  line `( iii ) where he is mentally incapacitated from attending to his affairs, by his guardian or any`
  line `other person competent to act on his behalf; and`
  line `( iv ) where, for any other reason, it is not possible for the individual to 1 [verify] the return, by`
  line `any person duly authorised by him in this behalf:`
  line `Provided that in a case referred to in sub-clause ( ii ) or sub-clause ( iv ), the person 2 [verifying]`
  line `the return holds a valid power of attorney from the individual to do so, which shall be attached to`
  line `the return;]`
  line `( b ) in the case of a Hindu undivided family, by the karta, and, where the karta is absent from`
  line `India or is mentally incapacitated from attending to his affairs, by any other adult member of such`
  line family;
  line `3 [( c ) in the case of a company, by the managing director thereof, or where for any unavoidable`
  line `reason such managing director is not able to 4 [verify]the return, or where there is no managing`
  line `director, by any director thereof:`
  line `5 [Provided that where the company is not resident in India, the return may be verified by a person`
  line `who holds a valid power of attorney from such company to do so, which shall be attached to the`
  line `return:`
  line `Provided further that, —`
  line `( a ) where the company is being wound up, whether under the orders of a court or otherwise,`
  line `or where any person has been appointed as the receiver of any assets of the company, the return`
  line `shall be 6 [verified] by the liquidator referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 178;`
  line `( b ) where the management of the company has been taken over by the Central Government or`
  line `any State Government under any law, the return of the company shall be 6 [verified] by the`
  line `principal officer thereof 7 [or];]`
  line `7 [( c ) where in respect of a company, an application for corporate insolvency resolution`
  line `process has been admitted by the Adjudicating Authority under section 7 or section 9 or section`
  line `10 of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016, the return shall be verified by the insolvency`
  line `professional appointed by such Adjudicating Authority.`
  line `Explanation. ––For the purposes of this clause the expressions “insolvency professional” and`
  line `“Adjudicating Authority” shall have the respective meanings assigned to them in clause ( 18 ) of`
  line `section 3 and clause ( 1 ) of section 5 of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016;]`
  line `( cc ) in the case of a firm, by the managing partner thereof, or where for any unavoidable`
  line `reason such managing partner is not able to 4 [verify] the return, or where there is no managing`
  line `partner as such, by any partner thereof, not being a minor;`
  line `8 [( cd ) in the case of a limited liability partnership, by the designated partner thereof, or where`
  line `for any unavoidable reason such designated partner is not able to 4 [verify] the return, or where`
  line `there is no designated partner as such, by any partner thereof;]`
  line `( d ) in the case of a local authority, by the principal officer thereof;]`
  line `9 [( dd ) in the case of a political party referred to in sub-section ( 4B ) of section 139, by the`
  line `chief executive officer of such party (whether such chief executive officer is known as secretary`
  line `or by any other designation);]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 50, for “sign” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2014).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 50, ibid., for “signing” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2014).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 40, for clauses ( c ) and ( d ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 50, for “sign and verify” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2014).`
  line `5. Added by Act 4 of 1988, s. 44 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 50, for “signed and verified” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2014).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 54 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 44 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
