obj_root_law_sections_572_content:
  string
  line 572
  line `( d ) any relief of tax claimed under section 90A on account of tax paid in any specified`
  line `territory outside India referred to in that section; and`
  line `( e ) any tax credit claimed to be set off in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `section 115JAA 1 [or section 115JD];]`
  line `( ii ) under section 115WK shall be computed on the amount of tax on the value of the fringe`
  line `benefits as declared in the return as reduced by the advance tax, paid, if any.]`
  line `( 1B ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), interest payable under section 234B shall be computed on an`
  line `amount equal to the assessed tax or, as the case may be, on the amount by which the advance tax paid`
  line `falls short of the assessed tax.`
  line `2 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- section, “assessed tax” means the tax on the total`
  line `income as declared in the return as reduced by the amount of, —`
  line `( i ) tax deducted or collected at source, in accordance with the provisions of Chapter XVII, on any`
  line `income which is subject to such deduction or collection and which is taken into account in computing`
  line `such total income;`
  line `( ii ) any relief of tax or deduction of tax claimed under section 90 or section 91 on account of tax`
  line `paid in a country outside India;`
  line `( iii ) any relief of tax claimed under section 90A on account of tax paid in any specified territory`
  line `outside India referred to in that section; and`
  line `( iv ) any tax credit claimed to be set off in accordance with the provisions of section`
  line `115JAA 1 [or section 115JD].]]`
  line `( 2 ) After a regular assessment under 3 [section 115WE or section 115WF or section 143] or`
  line `section 144 4 [or 5 [an assessment under section 153A or section 158BC]] has been made, any amount paid`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to have been paid towards such regular assessment 4 [or assessment,`
  line `as the case may be].`
  line `6 [( 3 ) If any assessee fails to pay the whole or any part of such tax or interest or both in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ), he shall, without prejudice to any other consequences which he`
  line `may incur, be deemed to be an assessee in default in respect of the tax or interest or both remaining`
  line `unpaid, and all the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly.]]`
  line `7 [( 4 ) The provisions of this section as they stood immediately before their amendment by the Direct`
  line `Tax Laws (Amendment) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988), shall apply to and in relation to any assessment for the`
  line `assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1988, or any earlier assessment year and references`
  line `in this section to the other provisions of this Act shall be construed as references to those provisions as for`
  line `the time being in force and applicable to the relevant assessment year.]`
  line `141. [ Provisional assessment.] — Omitted by the Taxation Laws (Amendment) Act, 1970, s. 28 ( w.e.f.`
  line `1-4-1971).`
  line `141A. [ Provisional assessment for refund.] — Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws (Amendment) Act,`
  line `1987, ( w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier section 141A was inserted by the Finance Act, 1968, s. 11 ( w.e.f. 1-4-`
  line `1968). Original section was inserted by the Finance Act, 1963, s. 9 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1963) and omitted by the`
  line `Finance Act, 1964, s. 35 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1964).`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 60 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 34, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 43, for “section 143” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 63 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 63 (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 45, for sub-section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 36 of 1989, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
