obj_root_law_sections_573_content:
  string
  line 573
  line `142. Inquiry before assessment. — ( 1 ) For the purpose of making an assessment under this Act, the`
  line `1 [Assessing Officer] may serve on any person who has made a return 2 [under section 115WD or`
  line `section 139 3 [or in whose case the time allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139] for furnishing the`
  line `return has expired] a notice requiring him, on a date to be therein specified, —`
  line `4 [( i ) where such person has not made a return 5 [ 6 [within the time allowed under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 139] or before the end of the relevant assessment year], to furnish a return of his income or`
  line `the income of any other person in respect of which he is assessable under this Act, in the prescribed`
  line `form and verified in the prescribed mannerand setting forth such other particulars as may be`
  line `prescribed, or:]`
  line `7 [ Provided that where any notice has been served under this sub-section for the purposes of this`
  line `clause after the end of the relevant assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 1990`
  line `to a person who has not made a return within the time allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139 or`
  line `before the end of the relevant assessment year, any such notice issued to him shall be deemed to have`
  line `been served in accordance with the provisions of this sub-section,]`
  line `8 [( ii )] to produce, or cause to be produced, such accounts or documents as the 1 [Assessing`
  line `Officer] may require, or`
  line `8 [( iii )] to furnish in writing and verified in the prescribed manner information in such form and on`
  line `such points or matters (including a statement of all assets and liabilities of the assessee, whether`
  line `included in the accounts or not) as the 1 [Assessing Officer] may require:`
  line `Provided that —`
  line `( a ) the previous approval of the 9 [Joint Commissioner] shall be obtained before requiring the`
  line `assessee to furnish a statement of all assets and liabilities not included in the accounts;`
  line `( b ) the 1 [Assessing Officer] shall not require the production of any accounts relating to a`
  line `period more than three years prior to the previous year.`
  line `( 2 ) For the purpose of obtaining full information in respect of the income or loss of any person, the`
  line `1 [Assessing Officer] may make such inquiry as he considers necessary.`
  line `10 [( 2A )If, at any stage of the proceedings before him, the 1 [Assessing Officer], having regard to 11 [the`
  line `nature and complexity of the accounts, volume of the accounts, doubts about the correctness of the`
  line `accounts, multiplicity of transactions in the accounts or specialised nature of business activity of the`
  line `assessee, and] the interests of the revenue, is of the opinion that it is necessary so to do, he may, with the`
  line `previous approval of the 12 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 13 [Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner], direct the assessee to get the accounts audited by an accountant, as`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Ac t 18 of 2005, s. 44, for “under section 139 or in whose case the time allowed under sub -section ( 1 ) of that`
  line `section” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 47, for “or to whom a notice has been issued under sub -section ( 2 ) of section 139 (whether a`
  line `return has been made or not)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 47, ibid (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 36, for “before the end of the relevant assessment year” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1990).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 35, for “within the time allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006)`
  line `7. Ins. by, s. 35, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `8. Clauses ( i ) and ( ii ) renumbered as clauses ( ii ) and ( iii ) thereof by Act 4 of 1988, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 3, f or “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10- 1998). Earlier substituted as “Deputy`
  line `Commissioner” for “Inspecting Assistant Commissioner” by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 43 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 37, for “the nature and complexity of the accounts of the assessee and” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `12. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013). Earlier substituted as Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner” for “Commissioner” by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `13. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
