obj_root_law_sections_574_content:
  string
  line 574
  line `defined in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288, nominated by the 1 [Principal Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 2 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] in this behalf and`
  line `to furnish a report of such audit in the prescribed formduly signed and verified by such accountant and`
  line `setting forth such particulars as may be prescribed and such other particulars as the 3 [Assessing Officer]`
  line `may require:`
  line `4 [Provided that the Assessing Officer shall not direct the assessee to get the accounts so audited`
  line `unless the assessee has been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard.]`
  line `( 2B ) The provisions of sub-section ( 2A ) shall have effect notwithstanding that the accounts of the`
  line `assessee have been audited under any other law for the time being in force or otherwise.`
  line `( 2C ) Every report under sub-section ( 2A ) shall be furnished by the assessee to the 3 [Assessing`
  line `Officer] within such period as may be specified by the 3 [Assessing Officer]:`
  line `Provided that the 3 [Assessing Officer] may, 5 [ suomotu, oron an application] made in this behalf by the`
  line `assessee and for any good and sufficient reason, extend the said period by such further period or periods`
  line `as he thinks fit; so, however, that the aggregate of the period originally fixed and the period or periods so`
  line `extended shall not, in any case, exceed one hundred and eighty days from the date on which the direction`
  line `under sub-section ( 2A ) is received by the assessee.`
  line `( 2D ) The expenses of, and incidental to, any audit under sub-section ( 2A ) (including the remuneration`
  line `of the accountant) shall be determined by the 1 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or`
  line `2 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] (which determination shall be final) and paid by the assessee`
  line `and in default of such payment, shall be recoverable from the assessee in the manner provided in Chapter`
  line `XVIID for the recovery of arrears of tax:]`
  line `4 [Provided that where any direction for audit under sub-section ( 2A ) is issued by the Assessing`
  line `Officer on or after the 1st day of June, 2007, the expenses of, and incidental to, such audit (including the`
  line `remuneration of the Accountant) shall be determined by the 1 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner] or 2 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] in accordance with such guidelines as`
  line `may be prescribedand the expenses so determined shall be paid by the Central Government.]`
  line `( 3 ) The assessee shall, except where the assessment is made under section 144, be given an`
  line `opportunity of being heard in respect of any material gathered on the basis of any inquiry under`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) 6 [or any audit under sub-section ( 2A )] and proposed to be utilised for the purposes of the`
  line assessment.
  line `7 [( 4 ) The provisions of this section as they stood immediately before their amendment by the Direct`
  line `Tax Laws (Amendment) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988), shall apply to and in relation to any assessment for the`
  line `assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1988, or any earlier assessment year and references`
  line `in this section to the other provisions of this Act shall be construed as references to those provisions as for`
  line `the time being in force and applicable to the relevant assessment year.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013). Earlier substituted as Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner” for “Commissioner” by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 46 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 31, for “on an application” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2008).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 43 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 36 of 1989, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
