obj_root_law_sections_575_content:
  string
  line 575
  line `1 [142A. Estimation of value of assets by Valuation Officer. — ( 1 ) The Assessing Officermay, for`
  line `the purposes of assessment or reassessment, make a reference to a Valuation Officer to estimate the value,`
  line `including fair market value, of any asset, property or investment and submit a copy of report to him.`
  line `( 2 ) The Assessing Officer may make a reference to the Valuation Officer under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `whether or not he is satisfied about the correctness or completeness of the accounts of the assessee.`
  line `( 3 ) The Valuation Officer, on a reference made under sub-section ( 1 ), shall, for the purpose of`
  line `estimating the value of the asset, property or investment, have all the powers that he has under section`
  line `38A of the Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957).`
  line `( 4 ) The Valuation Officer shall, estimate the value of the asset, property or investment after taking`
  line `into account such evidence as the assessee may produce and any other evidence in his possession`
  line `gathered, after giving an opportunity of being heard to the assessee.`
  line `( 5 ) The Valuation Officer may estimate the value of the asset, property or investment to the best of`
  line `his judgment, if the assessee does not co-operate or comply with his directions.`
  line `( 6 ) The Valuation Officer shall send a copy of the report of the estimate made under sub-section ( 4 )`
  line `or sub-section ( 5 ), as the case may be, to the Assessing Officer and the assessee, within a period of six`
  line `months from the end of the month in which a reference is made under sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 7 ) The Assessing Officer may, on receipt of the report from the Valuation Officer, and after giving`
  line `the assessee an opportunity of being heard, take into account such report in making the assessment or`
  line reassessment.
  line `Explanation. — In this section, “Valuation Officer” has the same meaning as in clause ( r ) of section 2`
  line `of the Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957).]`
  line `2 [143. Assessment. — 3 [( 1 ) Where a return has been made under section 139, or in response to a notice`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142, such return shall be processed in the following manner, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the total income or loss shall be computed after making the following adjustments, namely: —`
  line `( i ) any arithmetical error in the return; 4 ***`
  line `( ii ) an incorrect claim, if such incorrect claim is apparent from any information in the return;`
  line `5 [( iii ) disallowance of loss claimed, if return of the previous year for which set off of loss is`
  line `claimed was furnished beyond the due date specified under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139;`
  line `( iv ) disallowance of expenditure indicated in the audit report but not taken into account in`
  line `computing the total income in the return;`
  line `( v ) disallowance of deduction claimed under sections 10AA, 80-IA, 80-IAB, 80-IB,`
  line `80-IC, 80-ID or section 80-IE, if the return is furnished beyond the due date specified under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139; or`
  line `( vi ) addition of income appearing in Form 26AS or Form 16A or Form 16 which has not been`
  line `included in computing the total income in the return:`
  line `1. Subs by Act 25 of 2014, s. 51, for section 142A (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 48, for section 143 (w.e.f 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 32, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `4. The word “or” omitted by Act 28 of 2016, s. 68 (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 68, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
