obj_root_law_sections_578_content:
  string
  line 578
  line `( ii ) the approval granted to such 1 [research association] or other association 2 [or fund or trust] or`
  line `institution or university or other educational institution or hospital or other medical institution has`
  line `been withdrawn or notification issued in respect of such news agency or fund or trust or institution`
  line `has been rescinded:]`
  line `3 [Provided further that where the Assessing Officer is satisfied that the activities of the university,`
  line `college or other institution referred to in clause ( ii ) and clause ( iii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 35 are`
  line `not being carried out in accordance with all or any of the conditions subject to which such university,`
  line `college or other institution was approved, he may, after giving a reasonable opportunity of showing`
  line `cause against the proposed withdrawal to the concerned university, college or other institution,`
  line `recommend to the Central Government to withdraw the approval and that Government may by order,`
  line `withdraw the approval and forward a copy of the order to the concerned university, college or other`
  line `institution and the Assessing Officer:]`
  line `4 [Provided also that notwithstanding anything contained in the first and the second provisos, no`
  line `effect shall be given by the Assessing Officer to the provisions of clause ( 23C ) of section 10 in the`
  line `case of a trust or institution for a previous year, if the provisions of the first proviso to clause ( 15 ) of`
  line `section 2 become applicable in the case of such person in such previous year, whether or not the`
  line `approval granted to such trust or institution or notification issued in respect of such trust or institution`
  line `has been withdrawn or rescinded.]`
  line `5 [( 3A ) The Central Government may make a scheme, by notification in the Official Gazette, for the`
  line `purposes of making assessment of total income or loss of the assessee under sub-section ( 3 ) so as to`
  line `impart greater efficiency, transparency and accountability by ––`
  line `( a ) eliminating the interface between the Assessing Officer and the assessee in the course of`
  line `proceedings to the extent technologically feasible;`
  line `( b ) optimising utilisation of the resources through economies of scale and functional`
  line specialisation;
  line `( c ) introducing a team-based assessment with dynamic jurisdiction.`
  line `( 3B ) The Central Government may, for the purpose of giving effect to the scheme made under sub-`
  line `section ( 3A ), by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that any of the provisions of this Act relating to`
  line `assessment of total income or loss shall not apply or shall apply with such exceptions, modifications and`
  line `adaptations as may be specified in the notification: Provided that no direction shall be issued after the 31st`
  line `day of March, 2020.`
  line `( 3C ) Every notification issued under sub-section ( 3A ) and sub-section ( 3B ) shall, as soon as may be`
  line `after the notification is issued, be laid before each House of Parliament.]`
  line `6 [( 4 ) Where a regular assessment under sub-section ( 3 ) of this section or section 144 is made, —`
  line `( a ) any tax or interest paid by the assessee under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to have been`
  line `paid towards such regular assessment;`
  line `( b ) if no refund is due on regular assessment or the amount refunded under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `exceeds the amount refundable on regular assessment, the whole or the excess amount so refunded`
  line `shall be deemed to be tax payable by the assessee and the provisions of this Act shall apply`
  line accordingly.
  line `7 * * * * *]`
  line `8 * * * * *`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 34, for “scientific research association” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2011).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012 s. 61 (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 46 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 36 of 1989, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `7. Sub-section ( 5 ) omitted by Act 27 of 1999, s. 64 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `8. The Explanation omitted by s. 64, ibid (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
