obj_root_law_sections_579_content:
  string
  line 579
  line `144. Best judgment assessment. — 1 [ ( 1 )] If any person —`
  line `( a ) fails to make the return required 2 [under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139] and has not made a`
  line `return or a revised return under sub-section ( 4 ) or sub-section ( 5 ) of that section, or`
  line `( b ) fails to comply with all the terms of a notice issued under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142 3 [or`
  line `fails to comply with a direction issued under sub-section ( 2A ) of that section], or`
  line `( c ) having made a return, fails to comply with all the terms of a notice issued under sub-section`
  line `( 2 ) of section 143,`
  line `the 4 [Assessing Officer], after taking into account all relevant material which the 4 [Assessing Officer] has`
  line `gathered, 5 [shall, after giving the assessee an opportunity of being heard, make the assessment] of the`
  line `total income or loss to the best of his judgment and determine the sum payable by the assesse 6 *** on the`
  line `basis of such assessment:`
  line `7 [Provided that such opportunity shall be given by the Assessing Officer by serving a notice calling`
  line `upon the assessee to show cause, on a date and time to be specified in the notice, why the assessment`
  line `should not be completed to the best of his judgment:`
  line `Provided further that it shall not be necessary to give such opportunity in a case where a notice under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142 has been issued prior to the making of an assessment under this section.]`
  line `8 [( 2 ) The provisions of this section as they stood immediately before their amendment by the Direct`
  line `Tax Laws (Amendment) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988), shall apply to and in relation to any assessment for the`
  line `assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1988, or any earlier assessment year and references`
  line `in this section to the other provisions of this Act shall be construed as references to those provisions as for`
  line `the time being in force and applicable to the relevant assessment year.]`
  line `9 [ 144A. Power of 10 [Joint Commissioner] to issue directions in certain cases. — 11 *** A 10 [Joint`
  line `Commissioner] may, on his own motion or on a reference being made to him by the 4 [Assessing Officer]`
  line `or on the application of an assessee, call for and examine the record of any proceeding in which an`
  line `assessment is pending and, if he considers that, having regard to the nature of the case or the amount`
  line `involved or for any other reason, it is necessary or expedient so to do, he may issue such directions as he`
  line `thinks fit for the guidance of the 4 [Assessing Officer] to enable him to complete the assessment and such`
  line `directions shall be binding on the 4 [Assessing Officer]:`
  line `Provided that no directions which are prejudicial to the assessee shall be issued before an opportunity`
  line `is given to the assessee to be heard.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this 12 [section] no direction as to the lines on which an`
  line `investigation connected with the assessment should be made, shall be deemed to be a direction prejudicial`
  line `to the assessee.`
  line `13 * * * * *`
  line `1. Section 144 renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 36 of 1989, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 49, for “by any notice given under sub -section ( 2 ) of section 139” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 44 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 49, ibid., for “shall make the assessment” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `6. The words “or refundable to the assess” omitted by s. 49, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `7. Ins. by s. 49, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 36 of 1989, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 3, for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f.1 -10-1998). Earlier the quoted words were substituted`
  line `by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Inspecting Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `11. The brackets and figu res “( 1 )” omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 126 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `12. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 22, for “sub - section” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `13. Sub-section ( 2 ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
