obj_root_law_sections_580:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-580
  sectionNo (580)
  orderNo 580
  title `Page 580`
  content obj_root_law_sections_580_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_580_footnotes
  sourcePage 580
obj_root_law_sections_580_content:
  string
  line 580
  line `[144B. Reference to Deputy Commissioner in certain cases ]. — Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws`
  line `( Amendment ) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988), s. 51 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1989).]]`
  line `1 [ 144BA. Reference to 2 [Principal Commissioner orCommissioner ] in certain cases. — ( 1 ) If, the`
  line `Assessing Officer, at any stage of the assessment or reassessment proceedings before him having regard`
  line `to the material and evidence available, considers that it is necessary to declare an arrangement as an`
  line `impermissible avoidance arrangement and to determine the consequence of such an arrangement within`
  line `the meaning of Chapter X-A, then, he may make a reference to the 2 [Principal Commissioner`
  line `or Commissioner] in this regard.`
  line `( 2 ) The 2 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] shall, on receipt of a reference under sub-section`
  line `( 1 ), if he is of the opinion that the provisions of Chapter X-A are required to be invoked, issue a notice to`
  line `the assessee, setting out the reasons and basis of such opinion, for submitting objections, if any, and`
  line `providing an opportunity of being heard to the assessee within such period, not exceeding sixty days, as`
  line `may be specified in the notice.`
  line `( 3 ) If the assessee does not furnish any objection to the notice within the time specified in the notice`
  line `issued under sub-section ( 2 ), the 2 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] shall issue such directions`
  line `as he deems fit in respect of declaration of the arrangement to be an impermissible avoidance`
  line arrangement.
  line `( 4 ) In case the assessee objects to the proposed action, and the 2 [Principal Commissioner`
  line `or Commissioner] after hearing the assessee in the matter is not satisfied by the explanation of the`
  line `assessee, then, he shall make a reference in the matter to the Approving Panel for the purpose of`
  line `declaration of the arrangement as an impermissible avoidance arrangement.`
  line `( 5 ) If the 2 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] is satisfied, after having heard the assessee that`
  line `the provisions of Chapter X-A are not to be invoked, he shall by an order in writing, communicate the`
  line `same to the Assessing Officer with a copy to the assessee.`
  line `( 6 ) The Approving Panel, on receipt of a reference from the 2 [Principal Commissioner`
  line `or Commissioner] under sub-section ( 4 ), shall issue such directions, as it deems fit, in respect of the`
  line `declaration of the arrangement as an impermissible avoidance arrangement in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of Chapter X-A including specifying of the previous year or years to which such declaration of`
  line `an arrangement as an impermissible avoidance arrangement shall apply.`
  line `( 7 ) No direction under sub-section ( 6 ) shall be issued unless an opportunity of being heard is given to`
  line `the assessee and the Assessing Officer on such directions which are prejudicial to the interest of the`
  line `assessee or the interests of the revenue, as the case may be.`
  line `( 8 ) The Approving Panel may, before issuing any direction under sub-section ( 6 ), —`
  line `( i ) if it is of the opinion that any further inquiry in the matter is necessary, direct the 2 [Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner] to make such inquiry or cause the inquiry to be made by any other`
  line `income-tax authority and furnish a report containing the result of such inquiry to it; or`
  line `( ii ) call for and examine such records relating to the matter as it deems fit; or`
  line `( iii ) require the assessee to furnish such documents and evidence as it may direct.`
  line `( 9 ) If the members of the Approving Panel differ in opinion on any point, such point shall be decided`
  line `according to the opinion of the majority of the members.`
  line `( 10 ) The Assessing Officer, on receipt of directions of the 2 [Principal Commissioner`
  line `or Commissioner] under sub-section ( 3 ) or of the Approving Panel under sub-section ( 6 ), shall proceed to`
  line `complete the proceedings referred to in sub-section ( 1 )in accordance with such directions and the`
  line `provisions of Chapter X-A.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 39 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016). Earlier s. 144BA omitted by Act 17 of 2013, s. 38 (w.e.f. 1-4-2014) which`
  line `was inserted by Act 23 of 2012, s. 62 (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_580_footnotes:
