  line
obj_root_law_sections_581:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-581
  sectionNo (581)
  orderNo 581
  title `Page 581`
  content obj_root_law_sections_581_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_581_footnotes
  sourcePage 581
obj_root_law_sections_581_content:
  string
  line 581
  line `( 11 ) If any direction issued under sub-section ( 6 ) specifies that declaration of the arrangement as`
  line `impermissible avoidance arrangement is applicable for any previous year other than the previous year to`
  line `which the proceedings referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) pertains, then, the Assessing Officer while`
  line `completing any assessment or reassessment proceedings of the assessment year relevant to such other`
  line `previous year shall do so in accordance with such directions and the provisions of Chapter XA and it shall`
  line `not be necessary for him to seek fresh direction on the issue for the relevant assessment year.`
  line `( 12 ) No order of assessment or reassessment shall be passed by the Assessing Officer without the`
  line `prior approval of the 1 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner], if any tax consequences have been`
  line `determined in the order under the provisions of Chapter X-A.`
  line `( 13 ) The Approving Panel shall issue directions under sub-section ( 6 ) within a period of six months`
  line `from the end of the month in which the reference under sub-section ( 4 ) was received.`
  line `( 14 ) The directions issued by the Approving Panel under sub-section ( 6 ) shall be binding on —`
  line `( i ) theassessee; and`
  line `( ii ) the 1 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] and the income-tax authorities subordinate to`
  line him,
  line `and notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of the Act, no appeal under the Act shall`
  line `lie against such directions.`
  line `( 15 ) The Central Government shall, for the purposes of this section, constitute one or more`
  line `Approving Panels as may be necessary and each panel shall consist of three members including a`
  line Chairperson.
  line `( 16 ) The Chairperson of the Approving Panel shall be a person who is or has been a judge of a High`
  line `Court, and —`
  line `( i ) one member shall be a member of Indian Revenue Service not below the rank of 2 [Principal`
  line `Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] of Income-tax; and`
  line `( ii ) one member shall be an academic or scholar having special knowledge of matters, such as`
  line `direct taxes, business accounts and international trade practices.`
  line `( 17 ) The term of the Approving Panel shall ordinarily be for one year and may be extended from time`
  line `to time up to a period of three years.`
  line `( 18 ) The Chairperson and members of the Approving Panel shall meet, as and when required, to`
  line `consider the references made to the panel and shall be paid such remuneration as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 19 ) In addition to the powers conferred on the Approving Panel under this section, it shall have the`
  line `powers which are vested in the Authority for Advance Rulings under section 245U.`
  line `( 20 ) The Board shall provide to the Approving Panel such officials as may be necessary for the`
  line `efficient exercise of powers and discharge of functions of the Approving Panel under the Act.`
  line `( 21 ) The Board may make rules for the purposes of the constitution and efficient functioning of the`
  line `Approving Panel and expeditious disposal of the references received under sub-section ( 4 ).`
  line `Explanation. — In computing the period referred to in sub-section ( 13 ), the following shall be`
  line `excluded —`
  line `( i ) the period commencing from the date on which the first direction is issued by the Approving`
  line `Panel to the 1 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] for getting the inquiries conducted through`
  line `the authority competent under an agreement referred to in section 90 or section 90A and ending with`
  line `the date on which the information so requested is last received by the Approving Panel or one year,`
  line `whichever is less;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_581_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_582:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-582
  sectionNo (582)
  orderNo 582
  title `Page 582`
  content obj_root_law_sections_582_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_582_footnotes
  sourcePage 582
obj_root_law_sections_582_content:
  string
  line 582
  line `( ii ) the period during which the proceeding of the Approving Panel is stayed by an order or`
  line `injunction of any court:`
  line `Provided that where immediately after the exclusion of the aforesaid time or period, the period`
  line `available to the Approving Panel for issue of directions is less than sixty days, such remaining period`
  line `shall be extended to sixty days and the aforesaid period of six months shall be deemed to have been`
  line `extended accordingly.]`
  line `1 [ 144C. Reference to dispute resolution panel. — ( 1 ) The Assessing Officer shall, notwithstanding`
  line `anything to the contrary contained in this Act, in the first instance, forward a draft of the proposed order`
  line `of assessment (hereafter in this section referred to as the draft order) to the eligible assessee if he proposes`
  line `to make, on or after the 1st day of October, 2009, any variation in the income or loss returned which is`
  line `prejudicial to the interest of such assessee.`
  line `( 2 ) On receipt of the draft order, the eligible assessee shall, within thirty days of the receipt by him of`
  line `the draft order, —`
  line `( a ) file his acceptance of the variations to the Assessing Officer; or`
  line `( b ) file his objections, if any, to such variation with, —`
  line `( i ) the Dispute Resolution Panel; and`
  line `( ii ) the Assessing Officer.`
  line `( 3 ) The Assessing Officer shall complete the assessment on the basis of the draft order, if —`
  line `( a ) theassessee intimates to the Assessing Officer the acceptance of the variation; or`
  line `( b ) no objections are received within the period specified in sub-section ( 2 ).`
  line `( 4 ) The Assessing Officer shall, notwithstanding anything contained 2 [in section 153 orsection 153B],`
  line `pass the assessment order under sub-section ( 3 ) within one month from the end of the month in which, —`
  line `( a ) the acceptance is received; or`
  line `( b ) the period of filing of objections under sub-section ( 2 ) expires.`
  line `( 5 ) The Dispute Resolution Panel shall, in a case where any objection is received under`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ), issue such directions, as it thinks fit, for the guidance of the Assessing Officer to enable`
  line `him to complete the assessment.`
  line `( 6 ) The Dispute Resolution Panel shall issue the directions referred to in sub-section ( 5 ), after`
  line `considering the following, namely: —`
  line `( a ) draft order;`
  line `( b ) objections filed by the assessee;`
  line `( c ) evidence furnished by the assessee;`
  line `( d ) report, if any, of the Assessing Officer, Valuation Officer or Transfer Pricing Officer or any`
  line `other authority;`
  line `( e ) records relating to the draft order;`
  line `( f ) evidence collected by, or caused to be collected by, it; and`
  line `( g ) result of any enquiry made by, or caused to be made by, it.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 56 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 63, for “in section 153” (w.r.e.f. 1 -10-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_582_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_583:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-583
  sectionNo (583)
  orderNo 583
  title `Page 583`
  content obj_root_law_sections_583_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_583_footnotes
  sourcePage 583
obj_root_law_sections_583_content:
  string
  line 583
  line `( 7 ) The Dispute Resolution Panel may, before issuing any directions referred to in sub-section ( 5 ), —`
  line `( a ) make such further enquiry, as it thinks fit; or`
  line `( b ) cause any further enquiry to be made by any income-tax authority and report the result of the`
  line `same to it.`
  line `( 8 ) The Dispute Resolution Panel may confirm, reduce or enhance the variations proposed in the draft`
  line `order so, however, that it shall not set aside any proposed variation or issue any direction under sub-`
  line `section ( 5 ) for further enquiry and passing of the assessment order.`
  line `1 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the power of the Dispute`
  line `Resolution Panel to enhance the variation shall include and shall be deemed always to have included the`
  line `power to consider any matter arising out of the assessment proceedings relating to the draft order,`
  line `notwithstanding that such matter was raised or not by the eligible assessee.]`
  line `( 9 ) If the members of the Dispute Resolution Panel differ in opinion on any point, the point shall be`
  line `decided according to the opinion of the majority of the members.`
  line `( 10 ) Every direction issued by the Dispute Resolution Panel shall be binding on the Assessing`
  line Officer.
  line `( 11 ) No direction under sub-section ( 5 ) shall be issued unless an opportunity of being heard is given`
  line `to the assessee and the Assessing Officer on such directions which are prejudicial to the interest of the`
  line `assessee or the interest of the revenue, respectively.`
  line `( 12 ) No direction under sub-section ( 5 ) shall be issued after nine months from the end of the month in`
  line `which the draft order is forwarded to the eligible assessee.`
  line `( 13 ) Upon receipt of the directions issued under sub-section ( 5 ), the Assessing Officer shall, in`
  line `conformity with the directions, complete, notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained 2 [insection`
  line `153 or section 153B], the assessment without providing any further opportunity of being heard to the`
  line `assessee, within one month from the end of the month in which such direction is received.`
  line `( 14 ) The Board may make rules for the purposes of the efficient functioning of the Dispute`
  line `Resolution Panel and expeditious disposal of the objections filed under sub-section ( 2 ) by the eligible`
  line assessee.
  line `3 [( 14A )The provisions of this section shall not apply to any assessment or reassessment order passed`
  line `by the Assessing Officer with the prior approval of the 4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] as`
  line `provided in sub-section ( 12 ) of section 144BA.]`
  line `( 15 ) For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “Dispute Resolution Panel” means a collegium comprising of three 4 [Principal Commissioner`
  line `or Commissioners] of Income-tax constituted by the Board for this purpose;`
  line `( b ) “eligibleassessee” means,—`
  line `( i ) any person in whose case the variation referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) arises as a`
  line `consequence of the order of the Transfer Pricing Officer passed under sub-section ( 3 ) of`
  line `section 92CA; and`
  line `( ii ) any foreign company.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 63 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 63, ibid., for “in section 153” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2009).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016). Earlier sub-section ( 14A ) omitted by Act 17 of 2013, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-4-`
  line `2013) which was inserted by Act 23 of 2012, s. 63 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_583_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_584:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-584
  sectionNo (584)
  orderNo 584
  title `Page 584`
  content obj_root_law_sections_584_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_584_footnotes
  sourcePage 584
obj_root_law_sections_584_content:
  string
  line 584
  line `1 [ 145. Method of accounting. — ( 1 ) Income chargeable under the head “Profits and gains of business`
  line `or profession” or “Income from other sources” shall, subject to the provisions of sub -section ( 2 ), be`
  line `computed in accordance with either cash or mercantile system of accounting regularly employed by the`
  line assessee.
  line `( 2 ) The Central Government may notify in the Official Gazette from time to time 2 [income`
  line `computation and disclosure standards] to be followed by any class of assessees or in respect of any class`
  line `of income.`
  line `( 3 ) Where the Assessing Officer is not satisfied about the correctness or completeness of the accounts`
  line `of the assessee, or where the method of accounting provided in sub-section ( 1 ) 3 [has not been regularly`
  line `followed by the assessee, or income has not been computed in accordance with the standards notified`
  line `under sub-section ( 2 )], the Assessing Officer may make an assessment in the manner provided in`
  line `section 144.]`
  line `4 [ 145A. Method of accounting in certain cases. — For the purpose of determining the income`
  line `chargeable under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession”,––`
  line `( i ) the valuation of inventory shall be made at lower of actual cost or net realisable value`
  line `computed in accordance with the income computation and disclosure standards notified under`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 145;`
  line `( ii ) the valuation of purchase and sale of goods or services and of inventory shall be adjusted to`
  line `include the amount of any tax, duty, cess or fee (by whatever name called) actually paid or incurred`
  line `by the assessee to bring the goods or services to the place of its location and condition as on the date`
  line `of valuation;`
  line `( iii ) the inventory being securities not listed on a recognised stock exchange, or listed but not`
  line `quoted on a recognised stock exchange with regularity from time to time, shall be valued at actual`
  line `cost initially recognised in accordance with the income computation and disclosure standards notified`
  line `under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 145;`
  line `( iv ) the inventory being securities other than those referred to in clause ( iii ), shall be valued at`
  line `lower of actual cost or net realisable value in accordance with the income computation and disclosure`
  line `standards notified under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 145:`
  line `Provided that the inventory being securities held by a scheduled bank or public financial`
  line `institution shall be valued in accordance with the income computation and disclosure standards`
  line `notified under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 145 after taking into account the extant guidelines issued by`
  line `the Reserve Bank of India in this regard:`
  line `Provided further that the comparison of actual cost and net realisable value of securities shall be`
  line `made category-wise.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 31, for section 145 (w.e.f. 1-4-1997).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 52, for “accounting standards” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2015).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 52, ibid., for “or accounting standards as notified under sub -section ( 2 ), have not been regularly followed by`
  line `the assessee” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2015).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 47, for section 145A (w.r.e.f. 1-4-2017). Earlier it was substituted by Act 33 of 2009,`
  line `s. 57, (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_584_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_585:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-585
  sectionNo (585)
  orderNo 585
  title `Page 585`
  content obj_root_law_sections_585_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_585_footnotes
  sourcePage 585
obj_root_law_sections_585_content:
  string
  line 585
  line `Explanation 1. — For the purposes of this section, any tax, duty, cess or fee (by whatever name called)`
  line `under any law for the time being in force, shall include all such payment notwithstanding any right arising`
  line `as a consequence to such payment.`
  line `Explanation 2. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “ public financial institution ” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( 72 ) of section 2`
  line `of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013);`
  line `( b ) “ recognised stock exchange ” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( ii ) of`
  line `Explanation 1 to clause ( 5 ) of section 43;`
  line `( c ) “ scheduled bank ” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( ii ) of the Explanation to`
  line `clause ( viia ) of sub-section (1) of section 36.`
  line `145B. Taxability of certain income. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in`
  line `section 145, the interest received by an assessee on any compensation or on enhanced compensation, as`
  line `the case may be, shall be deemed to be the income of the previous year in which it is received.`
  line `( 2 ) Any claim for escalation of price in a contract or export incentives shall be deemed to be the`
  line `income of the previous year in which reasonable certainty of its realisation is achieved.`
  line `( 3 ) The income referred to in sub-clause ( xviii ) of clause ( 24 ) of section 2 shall be deemed to be the`
  line `income of the previous year in which it is received, if not charged to income-tax in any earlier previous`
  line year.]
  line `146. [ Reopening of assessment at the instance of the assessee.] Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws`
  line `( Amendment ) Act, 1988 (4 of 1988), s. 53 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989 ).`
  line `1 [ 147. Income escaping assessment. — If the 2 [Assessing Officer] 3 [has reason to believe] that any`
  line `income chargeable to tax has escaped assessment for any assessment year, he may, subject to the`
  line `provisions of sections 148 to 153, assess or reassess such income and also any other income chargeable to`
  line `tax which has escaped assessment and which comes to his notice subsequently in the course of the`
  line `proceedings under this section, or recompute the loss or the depreciation allowance or any other`
  line `allowance, as the case may be, for the assessment year concerned (hereafter in this section and in sections`
  line `148 to 153 referred to as the relevant assessment year):`
  line `Provided that where an assessment under sub-section ( 3 ) of section 143 or this section has been made`
  line `for the relevant assessment year, no action shall be taken under this section after the expiry of four years`
  line `from the end of the relevant assessment year, unless any income chargeable to tax has escaped assessment`
  line `for such assessment year by reason of the failure on the part of the assessee to make a return under`
  line `section 139 or in response to a notice issued undersub-section ( 1 ) of section 142 or section 148 or to`
  line `disclose fully and truly all material facts necessary for his assessment, for that assessment year:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 54, for sections 147 and 148 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 23, for “, for reasons to be recorded by him in writing, is of the opinion” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_585_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_586:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-586
  sectionNo (586)
  orderNo 586
  title `Page 586`
  content obj_root_law_sections_586_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_586_footnotes
  sourcePage 586
obj_root_law_sections_586_content:
  string
  line 586
  line `1 [ Provided further that nothing contained in the first proviso shall apply in a case where any income`
  line `in relation to any asset (including financial interest in any entity) located outside India, chargeable to tax,`
  line `has escaped assessment for any assessment year:]`
  line `2 [ 3 [Provided also] that the Assessing Officer may assess or reassess such income, other than`
  line `theincome involving matters which are the subject matters of any appeal, reference or revision, which is`
  line `chargeable to tax and has escaped assessment.]`
  line `Explanation 1. — Production before the Assessing Officer of account books or other evidence from`
  line `which material evidence could with due diligence have been discovered by the Assessing Officer will not`
  line `necessarily amount to disclosure within the meaning of the foregoing proviso.`
  line `Explanation 2. — For the purposes of this section, the following shall also be deemed to be cases`
  line `where income chargeable to tax has escaped assessment, namely: —`
  line `( a ) where no return of income has been furnished by the assessee although his total income or the`
  line `total income of any other person in respect of which he is assessable under this Act during the`
  line `previous year exceeded the maximum amount which is not chargeable to income-tax;`
  line `( b ) where a return of income has been furnished by the assessee but no assessment has been made`
  line `and it is noticed by the Assessing Officer that the assessee has understated the income or has claimed`
  line `excessive loss, deduction, allowance or relief in the return;`
  line `1 [( ba ) where the assessee has failed to furnish a report in respect of any international transaction`
  line `which he was so required under section 92E;]`
  line `( c ) where an assessment has been made, but —`
  line `( i ) income chargeable to tax has been underassessed; or`
  line `( ii ) such income has been assessed at too low a rate; or`
  line `( iii ) such income has been made the subject of excessive relief under this Act; or`
  line `( iv ) excessive loss or depreciation allowance or any other allowance under this Act has been`
  line computed;]
  line `4 [( ca ) where a return of income has not been furnished by the assessee or a return of income has`
  line `been furnished by him and on the basis of information or document received from the prescribed`
  line `income-tax authority, under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 133C, it is noticed by the Assessing Officer`
  line `that the income of the assessee exceeds the maximum amount not chargeable to tax, or as the case`
  line `may be, the assessee has understated the income or has claimed excessive loss, deduction, allowance`
  line `or relief in the return;]`
  line `1 [( d ) where a person is found to have any asset (including financial interest in any entity) located`
  line `outside India.]`
  line `5 [ Explanation 3. — For the purpose of assessment or reassessment under this section, the Assessing`
  line `Officer may assess or reassess the income in respect of any issue, which has escaped assessment, and`
  line `such issue comes to his notice subsequently in the course of the proceedings under this section,`
  line `notwithstanding that the reasons for such issue have not been included in the reasons recorded under`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 148.]`
  line `1 [ Explanation 4. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that the provisions of this section,`
  line `as amended by the Finance Act, 2012 (23 of 2012), shall also be applicable for any assessment year`
  line `beginning on or before the 1st day of April, 2012.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 64 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 64, for “Provided further” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 69 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `5. Ins. by 33 of 2009, s. 58 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
