  content obj_root_law_sections_587_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_587_footnotes
  sourcePage 587
obj_root_law_sections_587_content:
  string
  line 587
  line `148. Issue of notice where income has escaped assessment. — 1 [( 1 )] Before making the assessment,`
  line `reassessment or recomputation under section 147, the Assessing Officer shall serve on the assessee a`
  line `notice requiring him to furnish within such period, 2 *** as may be specified in the notice, a return of his`
  line `income or the income of any other person in respect of which he is assessable under this Act during the`
  line `previous year corresponding to the relevant assessment year, in the prescribed form and verified in the`
  line `prescribed manner and setting forth such other particulars as may be prescribed; and the provisions of this`
  line `Act shall, so far as may be, apply accordingly as if such return were a return required to be furnished`
  line `undersection 139:]`
  line `3 [Provided that in a case —`
  line `( a ) where a return has been furnished during the period commencing on the 1st day of October,`
  line `1991 and ending on the 30th day of September, 2005 in response to a notice served under this section,`
  line and
  line `( b ) subsequently a notice has been served under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 143 after the expiry of`
  line `twelve months specified in the proviso to sub-section ( 2 ) of section 143, as it stood immediately`
  line `before the amendment of said sub-section by the Finance Act, 2002 (20 of 2002) but before the expiry`
  line `of the time limit for making the assessment, re-assessment or recomputation as specified in`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 153, every such notice referred to in this clause shall be deemed to be a`
  line `valid notice:`
  line `Provided further that in a case —`
  line `( a ) where a return has been furnished during the period commencing on the 1st day of October,`
  line `1991 and ending on the 30th day of September, 2005, in response to a notice served under this`
  line `section, and`
  line `( b ) subsequently a notice has been served under clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 143 after`
  line `the expiry of twelve months specified in the proviso to clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 143,`
  line `but before the expiry of the time limit for making the assessment, reassessment or recomputation as`
  line `specified in sub-section ( 2 ) of section 153, every such notice referred to in this clause shall be deemed`
  line `to be a valid notice.]`
  line `4 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that nothing contained in the first`
  line `proviso or the second proviso shall apply to any return which has been furnished on or after the 1st day of`
  line `October, 2005 in response to a notice served under this section.]`
  line `5 [( 2 ) The Assessing Officer shall, before issuing any notice under this section, record his reasons for`
  line `doing so.]`
  line `149. Time limit for notice. — 6 [( 1 ) No notice under section 148 shall be issued for the relevant`
  line `assessment year, —`
  line `7 [( a ) if four years have elapsed from the end of the relevant assessment year, unless the case falls`
  line `under clause ( b ) 8 [or clause ( c )];`
  line `( b ) if four years, but not more than six years, have elapsed from the end of the relevant`
  line `assessment year unless the income chargeable to tax which has escaped assessment amounts to or is`
  line `likely to amount to one lakh rupees or more for that year;]`
  line `8 [( c ) if four years, but not more than sixteen years, have elapsed from the end of the relevant`
  line `assessment year unless the income in relation to any asset (including financial interest in any entity)`
  line `located outside India, chargeable to tax, has escaped assessment.]`
  line `1. Section 54 renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 3 of 1989, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. The words “not being less than thirty days,” omitted by Act 33 of 1996, s. 43 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 36, ibid (w.e.f. 1-10-2005).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 55, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 63, for clauses ( a ) and ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2001).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
