  sourcePage 588
obj_root_law_sections_588_content:
  string
  line 588
  line `Explanation. — In determining income chargeable to tax which has escaped assessment for the`
  line `purposes of this sub-section, the provisions of Explanation 2 of section 147 shall apply as they apply for`
  line `the purposes of that section.]`
  line `( 2 ) The provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) as to the issue of notice shall be subject to the provisions`
  line `of section 151.`
  line `( 3 ) If the person on whom a notice under section 148 is to be served is a person treated as the agent of`
  line `a non-resident under section 163 and the assessment, reassessment or recomputation to be made in`
  line `pursuance of the notice is to be made on him as the agent of such non-resident, the notice shall not be`
  line `issued after the expiry of a period of 1 [six years] from the end of the relevant assessment year.`
  line `2 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that the provisions of sub-sections`
  line `( 1 ) and ( 3 ), as amended by the Finance Act, 2012, shall also be applicable for any assessment year`
  line `beginning on or before the 1st day of April, 2012.]`
  line `150. Provision for cases where assessment is in pursuance of an order on appeal, etc. — ( 1 )`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 149, the notice under section 148 may be issued at any`
  line `time for the purpose of making an assessment or reassessment or recomputation in consequence of or to`
  line `give effect to any finding or direction contained in an order passed by any authority in any proceeding`
  line `under this Act by way of appeal, reference or revision 3 [or by a Court in any proceeding under any other`
  line law].
  line `( 2 ) The provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) shall not apply in any case where any such assessment,`
  line `reassessment or recomputation as is referred to in that sub-section relates to an assessment year in respect`
  line `of which an assessment, reassessment or recomputation could not have been made at the time the order`
  line `which was the subject-matter of the appeal, reference or revision, as the case may be, was made by reason`
  line `of any other provision limiting the time within which any action for assessment, reassessment or`
  line `recomputation may be taken.`
  line `4 [ 151.Sanction for issue of notice. — ( 1 ) No notice shall be issued under section 148 by an Assessing`
  line `Officer, after the expiry of a period of four years from the end of the relevant assessment year, unless the`
  line `Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner or Principal Commissioner or Commissioner is`
  line `satisfied, on the reasons recorded by the Assessing Officer, that it is a fit case for the issue of such notice.`
  line `( 2 ) In a case other than a case falling under sub-section ( 1 ), no notice shall be issued under`
  line `section 148 by an Assessing Officer, who is below the rank of Joint Commissioner, unless the Joint`
  line `Commissioner is satisfied, on the reasons recorded by such Assessing Officer, that it is a fit case for the`
  line `issue of such notice.`
  line `( 3 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ) and sub-section ( 2 ), the Principal Chief Commissioner or the`
  line `Chief Commissioner or the Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner or the Joint Commissioner, as`
  line `the case may be, being satisfied on the reasons recorded by the Assessing Officer about fitness of a case`
  line `for the issue of notice under section 148, need not issue such notice himself.]`
  line `152. Other provisions. — ( 1 ) In an assessment, reassessment or recomputation made under`
  line `section 147, the tax shall be chargeable at the rate or rates at which it would have been charged had the`
  line `income not escaped assessment.`
  line `( 2 ) Where an assessment is reopened 5 [under section 147], the assessee may, if he has not impugned`
  line `any part of the original assessment order for that year either under sections 246 to 248 or under section`
  line `264, claim that the proceedings under section 147 shall be dropped on his showing that he had been`
  line `assessed on an amount or to a sum not lower than what he would be rightly liable for even if the income`
  line `alleged to have escaped assessment had been taken into account, or the assessment or computation had`
  line `been properly made:`
  line `Provided that in so doing he shall not be entitled to reopen matters concluded by an order`
  line `under section 154, 155, 260, 262, or 263.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 65, for “two years” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 65, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `3. Added by Act 4 of 1988, s. 56 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 36, for section 151 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 58, for “in circumstances falling under clause ( b ) of section 147” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
