obj_root_law_sections_589_content:
  string
  line 589
  line `1 [153. Time limit for completion of assessment, reassessment and recomputation. — ( 1 ) No order`
  line `of assessment shall be made under section 143 or section 144 at any time after the expiry of twenty-one`
  line `months from the end of the assessment year in which the income was first assessable:`
  line `2 [Provided that in respect of an order of assessment relating to the assessment year commencing on`
  line `the 1st day of April, 2018, the provisions of this sub- section shall have effect, as if for the words “twenty -`
  line `one months”, the words “eighteen months” had been substituted:`
  line `Provided further that in respect of an order of assessment relating to the assessment year commencing`
  line `on or after the 1st day of April, 2019, the provisions of this sub-section shall have effect, as if for the`
  line `words “twenty - one months”, the words “twelve months” had been substituted. ]`
  line `( 2 ) No order of assessment, reassessment or recomputation shall be made under section 147 after the`
  line `expiry of nine months from the end of the financial year in which the notice under section 148 was`
  line `served:`
  line `2 [Provided that where the notice under section 148 is served on or after the 1st day of April, 2019, the`
  line `provisions of this sub-section s hall have effect, as if for the words “nine months”, the words “twelve`
  line `months” had been substituted. ]`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ), an order of fresh assessment in`
  line `pursuance of an order under section 254 or section 263 or section 264, setting aside or cancelling an`
  line `assessment, may be made at any time before the expiry of nine months from the end of the financial year`
  line `in which the order under section 254 is received by the Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Principal Commissioner or Commissioner or, as the case may be, the order`
  line `under section 263 or section 264 is passed by the Principal Commissioner or Commissioner:`
  line `2 [Provided that where the order under section 254 is received by the Principal Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Chief Commissioner or Principal Commissioner or Commissioner or, as the case may be, the order`
  line `under section 263 or section 264 is passed by the Principal Commissioner or Commissioner on or after`
  line `the 1st day of April, 2019, the provisions of this sub- section shall have effect, as if for the words “nine`
  line `months”, the words “twelve months” had been substituted. ]`
  line `( 4 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections ( 1 ), ( 2 ) and ( 3 ), where a reference under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 92CA is made during the course of the proceeding for the assessment or`
  line `reassessment, the period available for completion of assessment or reassessment, as the case may be,`
  line `under the said sub-sections ( 1 ), ( 2 ) and ( 3 ) shall be extended by twelve months.`
  line `( 5 ) Where effect to an order under section 250 or section 254 or section 260 or section 262 or`
  line `section 263 or section 264 is to be given by the Assessing Officer, wholly or partly, otherwise than by`
  line `making a fresh assessment or reassessment, such effect shall be given within a period of three months`
  line `from the end of the month in which order under section 250 or section 254 or section 260 or`
  line `section 262 is received by the Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner or Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner, as the case may be, the order under section 263 or section 264 is passed`
  line `by the Principal Commissioner or Commissioner:`
  line `Provided that where it is not possible for the Assessing Officer to give effect to such order within the`
  line `aforesaid period, for reasons beyond his control, the Principal Commissioner or Commissioner on receipt`
  line `of such request in writing from the Assessing Officer, if satisfied, may allow an additional period of six`
  line `months to give effect to the order:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 70, for section 153 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 59 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
