obj_root_law_sections_590_content:
  string
  line 590
  line `1 [Provided further that where an order under section 250 or section 254 or section 260 or`
  line `section 262 or section 263 or section 264 requires verification of any issue by way of submission of`
  line `anydocument by the assessee or any other person or where an opportunity of being heard is to be`
  line `provided to the assessee, the order giving effect to the said order under section 250 or section 254 or`
  line `section 260 or section 262 or section 263 or section 264 shall be made within the time specifiedin sub-`
  line `section ( 3 ).]`
  line `( 6 ) Nothing contained in sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) shall apply to the following classes of assessments,`
  line `reassessments and recomputation which may, subject to the provisions of sub-sections ( 3 ) and ( 5 ), be`
  line `completed —`
  line `( i ) where the assessment, reassessment or recomputation is made on the assessee or any person in`
  line `consequence of or to give effect to any finding or direction contained in an order under`
  line `section 250, section 254, section 260, section 262, section 263, or section 264 or in an order of any`
  line `court in a proceeding otherwise than by way of appeal or reference under this Act, on or before the`
  line `expiry of twelve months from the end of the month in which such order is received or passed by the`
  line `Principal Commissioner or Commissioner, as the case may be; or`
  line `( ii ) where, in the case of a firm, an assessment is made on a partner of the firm in consequence of`
  line `an assessment made on the firm under section 147, on or before the expiry of twelve months from the`
  line `end of the month in which the assessment order in the case of the firm is passed.`
  line `( 7 ) Where effect to any order, finding or direction referred to in sub-section ( 5 ) or sub-section ( 6 ) is`
  line `to be given by the Assessing Officer, within the time specified in the said sub-sections, and such order has`
  line `been received or passed, as the case may be, by the income-tax authority specified therein before the 1st`
  line `day of June, 2016, the Assessing Officer shall give effect to such order, finding or direction, or assess,`
  line `reassess or recompute the income of the assessee, on or before the 31st day of March, 2017.`
  line `( 8 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 153A or sub-section ( 1 ) of section 153B, the order of assessment or reassessment, relating to`
  line `any assessment year, which stands revived under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 153A, shall be made within a`
  line `period of one year from the end of the month of such revival or within the period specified in this`
  line `section or sub-section ( 1 ) ofsection 153B, whichever is later.`
  line `( 9 ) The provisions of this section as they stood immediately before the commencement of the Finance`
  line `Act, 2016, shall apply to and in relation to any order of assessment, reassessment or recomputation made`
  line `before the 1st day of June, 2016:`
  line `1 [Provided that where a notice under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142 or sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 143 or section 148 has been issued prior to the 1st day of June, 2016 and the assessment or`
  line `reassessment has not been completed by such date due to exclusion of time referred to in Explanation 1,`
  line `such assessment or reassessment shall be completed in accordance with the provisions of this section as it`
  line `stood immediately before its substitution by the Finance Act, 2016 (28 of 2016).]`
  line `Explanation 1. — For the purposes of this section, in computing the period of limitation —`
  line `( i ) the time taken in reopening the whole or any part of the proceeding or in giving an opportunity`
  line `to the assessee to be re-heard under the proviso to section 129; or`
  line `( ii ) the period during which the assessment proceeding is stayed by an order or injunction of any`
  line `court; or`
  line `( iii ) the period commencing from the date on which the Assessing Officer intimates the Central`
  line `Government or the prescribed authority, the contravention of the provisions of clause ( 21 ) or clause`
  line `( 22B ) or clause ( 23A ) or clause ( 23B ) or sub-clause ( iv ) or sub-clause ( v ) or sub-clause ( vi ) or`
  line `sub-clause ( via ) of clause ( 23C ) of section 10, under clause ( i ) of the proviso to sub-section ( 3 )`
  line `of section 143 and ending with the date on which the copy of the order withdrawing the approval or`
  line `rescinding the notification, as the case may be, under those clauses is received by the Assessing`
  line `Officer; or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 59 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
