obj_root_law_sections_591_content:
  string
  line 591
  line `( iv ) the period commencing from the date on which the Assessing Officer directs the assessee to`
  line `get his accounts audited under sub-section ( 2A ) of section 142 and —`
  line `( a ) ending with the last date on which the assessee is required to furnish a report of such audit`
  line `under that sub-section; or`
  line `( b ) where such direction is challenged before a court, ending with the date on which the order`
  line `setting aside such direction is received by the Principal Commissioner or Commissioner; or`
  line `( v ) the period commencing from the date on which the Assessing Officer makes a reference to the`
  line `Valuation Officer under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142A and ending with the date on which the report`
  line `of the Valuation Officer is received by the Assessing Officer; or`
  line `( vi ) the period (not exceeding sixty days) commencing from the date on which the Assessing`
  line `Officer received the declaration under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 158A and ending with the date on`
  line `which the order under sub-section ( 3 ) of that section is made by him; or`
  line `( vii ) in a case where an application made before the Income-tax Settlement Commission is`
  line `rejected by it or is not allowed to be proceeded with by it, the period commencing from the date on`
  line `which an application is made before the Settlement Commission under section 245C and ending with`
  line `the date on which the order under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 245D is received by the Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner under sub-section ( 2 ) of that section; or`
  line `( viii ) the period commencing from the date on which an application is made before the Authority`
  line `for Advance Rulings under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 245Q and ending with the date on which the`
  line `order rejecting the application is received by the Principal Commissioner or Commissioner under`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ) of section 245R; or`
  line `( ix ) the period commencing from the date on which an application is made before the Authority`
  line `for Advance Rulings under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 245Q and ending with the date on which the`
  line `advance ruling pronounced by it is received by the Principal Commissioner or Commissioner under`
  line `sub-section ( 7 ) of section 245R; or`
  line `( x ) the period commencing from the date on which a reference or first of the references for`
  line `exchange of information is made by an authority competent under an agreement referred to in section`
  line `90 or section 90A and ending with the date on which the information requested is last received by the`
  line `Principal Commissioner or Commissioner or a period of one year, whichever is less; or`
  line `( xi ) the period commencing from the date on which a reference for declaration of an arrangement`
  line `to be an impermissible avoidance arrangement is received by the Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 144BA and ending on the date on which a direction`
  line `under sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 6 ) or an order under sub-section ( 5 ) of the said section is`
  line `received by the Assessing Officer,`
  line `shall be excluded:`
  line `Provided that where immediately after the exclusion of the aforesaid period, the period of limitation`
  line `referred to in sub-sections ( 1 ), ( 2 ), ( 3 ) and sub-section ( 8 ) available to the Assessing Officer for making`
  line `an order of assessment, reassessment or recomputation, as the case may be, is less than sixty days, such`
  line `remaining period shall be extended to sixty days and the aforesaid period of limitation shall be deemed to`
  line `be extended accordingly:`
obj_root_law_sections_591_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_592:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-592
