  title `Page 592`
  content obj_root_law_sections_592_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_592_footnotes
  sourcePage 592
obj_root_law_sections_592_content:
  string
  line 592
  line `Provided further that where the period available to the Transfer Pricing Officer is extended to sixty`
  line `days in accordance with the proviso to sub-section ( 3A ) of section 92CA and the period of limitation`
  line `available to the Assessing Officer for making an order of assessment, reassessment or recomputation, as`
  line `the case may be, is less than sixty days, such remaining period shall be extended to sixty days and the`
  line `aforesaid period of limitation shall be deemed to be extended accordingly:`
  line `Provided also that where a proceeding before the Settlement Commission abates under`
  line `section 245HA, the period of limitation available under this section to the Assessing Officer for making`
  line `an order of assessment, reassessment or recomputation, as the case may be, shall, after the exclusion of`
  line `the period under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 245HA, be not less than one year; and where such period of`
  line `limitation is less than one year, it shall be deemed to have been extended to one year; and for the purposes`
  line `of determining the period of limitation under sections 149, 1 *** 154, 155 and 158BE and for the purposes`
  line `of payment of interest under section 244A, this proviso shall also apply accordingly.`
  line `Explanation 2. — For the purposes of this section, where, by an order referred to in clause ( i ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 6 ), —`
  line `( a ) any income is excluded from the total income of the assessee for an assessment year, then, an`
  line `assessment of such income for another assessment year shall, for the purposes of section 150 and this`
  line `section, be deemed to be one made in consequence of or to give effect to any finding or direction`
  line `contained in the said order; or`
  line `( b ) any income is excluded from the total income of one person and held to be the income of`
  line `another person, then, an assessment of such income on such other person shall, for the purposes`
  line `of section 150 and this section, be deemed to be one made in consequence of or to give effect to any`
  line `finding or direction contained in the said order, if such other person was given an opportunity of`
  line `being heard before the said order was passed.]`
  line `2 [ 153A. Assessment in case of search or requisition. — 3 [( 1 )] Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `ssection139, section 147, section 148, section 149, section 151 and section 153, in the case of a person`
  line `where a search is initiated under section 132 or books of account, other documents or any assets are`
  line `requisitioned under section 132A after the 31st day of May, 2003, the Assessing Officer shall —`
  line `( a ) issue notice to such person requiring him to furnish within such period, as may be specified in`
  line `the notice, the return of income in respect of each assessment year falling within six assessment years`
  line `4 [and for the relevant assessment year or years] referred to in clause ( b ), in the prescribed form and`
  line `verified in the prescribed manner and setting forth such other particulars as may be prescribed and the`
  line `provisions of this Act shall, so far as may be, apply accordingly as if such return were a return`
  line `required to be furnished under section 139;`
  line `( b ) assess or reassess the total income of six assessment years immediately preceding the`
  line `assessment year relevant to the previous year in which such search is conducted or requisition is made`
  line `4 [and for the relevant assessment year or years]:`
  line `Provided that the Assessing Officer shall assess or reassess the total income in respect of each`
  line `assessment year falling within such six assessment years 4 [and for the relevant assessment year or`
  line `years]:`
  line `1. The figures and letter “153B,” omitted by Act 7 of 2017, s. 59 (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line `3. Section 153A renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 18 of 2008, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 60 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_592_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_593:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-593
  sectionNo (593)
  orderNo 593
  title `Page 593`
  content obj_root_law_sections_593_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_593_footnotes
  sourcePage 593
obj_root_law_sections_593_content:
  string
  line 593
  line `Provided further that assessment or reassessment, if any, relating to any assessment year falling`
  line `within the period of six assessment years 1 [and for the relevant assessment year or years] 2 [referred to`
  line `in this sub-section] pending on the date of initiation of the search under section 132 or making of`
  line `requisition under section 132A, as the case may be, shall abate:`
  line `3 [Provided also that the Central Government may by rulesmade by it and published in the Official`
  line `Gazette (except in cases where any assessment or reassessment has abated under the second proviso),`
  line `specify the class or classes of cases in which the Assessing Officer shall not be required to issue`
  line `notice for assessing or reassessing the total income for six assessment years immediately preceding`
  line `the assessment year relevant to the previous year in which search is conducted or requisition is made`
  line `1 [and for the relevant assessment year or years]:`
  line `1 [Provided also that no notice for assessment or reassessment shall be issued by the Assessing`
  line `Officer for the relevant assessment year or years unless —`
  line `( a ) the Assessing Officer has in his possession books of account or other documents or`
  line `evidence which reveal that the income, represented in the form of asset, which has escaped`
  line `assessment amounts to or is likely to amount to fifty lakh rupees or more in the relevant`
  line `assessment year or in aggregate in the relevant assessment years;`
  line `( b ) the income referred to in clause ( a ) or part thereof has escaped assessment for such year`
  line `or years; and`
  line `( c ) the search under section 132 is initiated or requisition under section 132A is made on or`
  line `after the 1st day of April, 2017.`
  line `Explanation 1. — For the purposes of this sub- section, the expression “relevant assessment year” shall`
  line `mean an assessment year preceding the assessment year relevant to the previous year in which search is`
  line `conducted or requisition is made which falls beyond six assessment years but not later than ten`
  line `assessment years from the end of the assessment year relevant to the previous year in which search is`
  line `conducted or requisition is made.`
  line `Explanation 2. —For the purposes of the fourth proviso, “asset” shall include immovable property`
  line `being land or building or both, shares and securities, loans and advances, deposits in bank account.]`
  line `4 [( 2 ) If any proceeding initiated or any order of assessment or reassessment made under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) has been annulled in appeal or any other legal proceeding, then, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in sub-section ( 1 ) or section 153, the assessment or reassessment relating to any assessment`
  line `year which has abated under the second proviso to sub-section ( 1 ), shall stand revived with effect from`
  line `the date of receipt of the order of such annulment by the 5 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]:`
  line `Provided that such revival shall cease to have effect, if such order of annulment is set aside.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that, —`
  line `( i ) save as otherwise provided in this section, section 153B and section 153C, all other provisions`
  line `of this Act shall apply to the assessment made under this section;`
  line `( ii ) in an assessment or reassessment made in respect of an assessment year under this section, the`
  line `tax shall be chargeable at the rate or rates as applicable to such assessment year.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 60 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 20 08, s. 36, for “referred to in this section” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2003).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 67 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_593_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_594:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-594
  sectionNo (594)
  orderNo 594
  title `Page 594`
  content obj_root_law_sections_594_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_594_footnotes
  sourcePage 594
obj_root_law_sections_594_content:
  string
  line 594
  line `1 [153B. Time limit for completion of assessment under section 153A. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in section 153, the Assessing Officer shall make an order of assessment or`
  line `reassessment, —`
  line `( a ) in respect of each assessment year falling within six assessment years 2 [ and for the relevant`
  line `assessment year or years ] referred to in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 153A, within a period`
  line `of twenty-one months from the end of the financial year in which the last of the authorisations for`
  line `search under section 132 or for requisition under section 132A was executed;`
  line `( b ) in respect of the assessment year relevant to the previous year in which search is conducted`
  line `under section 132 or requisition is made under section 132A, within a period of twenty-one months`
  line `from the end of the financial year in which the last of the authorisations for search under section`
  line `132 or for requisition under section 132A was executed:`
  line `Provided that in case of other person referred to in section 153C, the period of limitation for making`
  line `the assessment or reassessment shall be the period as referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of this`
  line `sub-section or nine months from the end of the financial year in which books of account or documents or`
  line `assets seized or requisitioned are handed over under section 153C to the Assessing Officer having`
  line `jurisdiction over such other person, whichever is later:`
  line `3 [ Provided further that in the case where the last of the authorisations for search under section 132 or`
  line `for requisition under section 132A was executed during the financial year commencing on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2018, —`
  line `( i ) the provisions of clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of this sub-section shall have effect, as if for the`
  line `words “twenty - one months”, the words “eighteen months” had been substituted;`
  line `( ii ) the period of limitation for making the assessment or reassessment in case of other person`
  line `referred to in section 153C, shall be the period of eighteen months from the end of the financial year`
  line `in which the last of the authorisations for search under section 132 or for requisition under`
  line `section 132A was executed or twelve months from the end of the financial year in which books of`
  line `account or documents or assets seized or requisitioned are handed over under section 153C to the`
  line `Assessing Officer having jurisdiction over such other person, whichever is later:`
  line `Provided also that in the case where the last of the authorisations for search under section 132 or for`
  line `requisition under section 132A was executed during the financial year commencing on or after the 1st day`
  line `of April, 2019, —`
  line `( i ) the provisions of clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of this sub-section shall have effect, as if for the`
  line `words “twenty - one months”, the words “twelve months” had been substituted;`
  line `( ii ) the period of limitation for making the assessment or reassessment in case of other person referred`
  line `to in section 153C, shall be the period of twelve months from the end of the financial year in which the last`
  line `of the authorisations for search under section 132 or for requisition under section 132A was executed or`
  line `twelve months from the end of the financial year in which books of account or documents or assets seized`
  line `or requisitioned are handed over under section 153C to the Assessing Officer having jurisdiction over such`
  line `other person, whichever is later:`
  line `Provided also that in case where the last of the authorisations for search under section 132 or for`
  line `requisition under section 132A was executed and during the course of the proceedings for the`
  line `assessment or reassessment of total income, a reference under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 92CA is made,`
  line `the period available for making an order of assessment or reassessment shall be extended by twelve`
  line `months:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 71, for section 153B (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 61 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `3. Subs by s. 61, ibid., for the second and third provisos (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_594_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_595:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-595
  sectionNo (595)
  orderNo 595
  title `Page 595`
  content obj_root_law_sections_595_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_595_footnotes
  sourcePage 595
obj_root_law_sections_595_content:
  string
  line 595
  line `Provided also that in case where during the course of the proceedings for the assessment or`
  line `reassessment of total income in case of other person referred to in section 153C, a reference under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 92CA is made, the period available for making an order of assessment or`
  line `reassessment in case of such other person shall be extended by twelve months:]`
  line `Provided also that in case where the last of the authorisations for search under section 132 or for`
  line `requisition under section 132A was executed and during the course of the proceedings for the`
  line `assessment or reassessment of total income, a reference under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 92CA is`
  line `made, the period available for making an order of assessment or reassessment shall be extended by`
  line `twelve months:`
  line `Provided also that in case where during the course of the proceedings for the assessment or`
  line `reassessment of total income in case of other person referred to in section 153C, a reference under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 92CA is made, the period available for making an order of assessment or`
  line `reassessment in case of such other person shall be extended by twelve months. ]`
  line `( 2 ) The authorisation referred to in clause ( a ) and clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to`
  line `have been executed, —`
  line `( a ) in the case of search, on the conclusion of search as recorded in the last panchnama drawn in`
  line `relation to any person in whose case the warrant of authorisation has been issued; or`
  line `( b ) in the case of requisition under section 132A, on the actual receipt of the books of account or`
  line `other documents or assets by the Authorised Officer.`
  line `( 3 ) The provisions of this section, as they stood immediately before the commencement of the`
  line `Finance Act, 2016, shall apply to and in relation to any order of assessment or reassessment made before`
  line `the 1st day of June, 2016:`
  line `1 [Provided that where a notice under section 153A or section 153C has been issued prior to the 1st`
  line `day of June, 2016 and the assessment has not been completed by such date due to exclusion of time`
  line `referred to in the Explanation, such assessment shall be completed in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `this section as it stood immediately before its substitution by the Finance Act, 2016 (28 of 2016).]`
  line `Explanation. — In computing the period of limitation under this section —`
  line `( i ) the period during which the assessment proceeding is stayed by an order or injunction of any`
  line `court; or`
  line `( ii ) the period commencing from the date on which the Assessing Officer directs the assessee to`
  line `get his accounts audited under sub-section ( 2A ) of section 142 and —`
  line `( a ) ending with the last date on which the assessee is required to furnish a report of such audit`
  line `under that sub-section; or`
  line `( b ) where such direction is challenged before a court, ending with the date on which the order`
  line `setting aside such direction is received by the Principal Commissioner or Commissioner; or`
  line `( iii ) the period commencing from the date on which the Assessing Officer makes a reference to`
  line `the Valuation Officer under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142A and ending with the date on which the`
  line `report of the Valuation Officer is received by the Assessing Officer; or`
  line `( iv ) the time taken in re-opening the whole or any part of the proceeding or in giving an`
  line `opportunity to the assessee of being re-heard under the proviso to section 129; or`
  line `( v ) in a case where an application made before the Income-tax Settlement Commission is rejected`
  line `by it or is not allowed to be proceeded with by it, the period commencing from the date on which an`
  line `application is made before the Settlement Commission under section 245C and ending with the date`
  line `on which the order under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 245D is received by the Principal Commissioner`
  line `or Commissioner under sub-section ( 2 ) of that section; or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 61 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_595_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_596:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-596
  sectionNo (596)
