  title `Page 596`
  content obj_root_law_sections_596_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_596_footnotes
  sourcePage 596
obj_root_law_sections_596_content:
  string
  line 596
  line `( vi ) the period commencing from the date on which an application is made before the Authority`
  line `for Advance Rulings under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 245Q and ending with the date on which the`
  line `order rejecting the application is received by the Principal Commissioner or Commissioner under`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ) of section 245R; or`
  line `( vii ) the period commencing from the date on which an application is made before the Authority`
  line `for Advance Rulings under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 245Q and ending with the date on which the`
  line `advance ruling pronounced by it is received by the Principal Commissioner or Commissioner under`
  line `sub-section ( 7 ) of section 245R; or`
  line `( viii ) the period commencing from the date of annulment of a proceeding or order of assessment`
  line `or reassessment referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) of section 153A, till the date of the receipt of the order`
  line `setting aside the order of such annulment, by the Principal Commissioner or Commissioner; or`
  line `( ix ) the period commencing from the date on which a reference or first of the references for`
  line `exchange of information is made by an authority competent under an agreement referred to in`
  line `section 90 or section 90A and ending with the date on which the information requested is last`
  line `received by the Principal Commissioner or Commissioner or a period of one year, whichever is less;`
  line or
  line `( x ) the period commencing from the date on which a reference for declaration of an arrangement`
  line `to be an impermissible avoidance arrangement is received by the Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 144BA and ending on the date on which a direction`
  line `under sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 6 ) or an order under sub-section ( 5 ) of the said section is`
  line `received by the Assessing Officer,`
  line `shall be excluded:`
  line `Provided that where immediately after the exclusion of the aforesaid period, the period of limitation`
  line `referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of this sub-section available to the Assessing Officer for making an`
  line `order of assessment or reassessment, as the case may be, is less than sixty days, such remaining period`
  line `shall be extended to sixty days and the aforesaid period of limitation shall be deemed to be extended`
  line `accordingly:`
  line `Provided further that where the period available to the Transfer Pricing Officer is extended to sixty`
  line `days in accordance with the proviso to sub-section ( 3A ) of section 92CA and the period of limitation`
  line `available to the Assessing Officer for making an order of assessment or reassessment, as the case may be,`
  line `is less than sixty days, such remaining period shall be extended to sixty days and the aforesaid period of`
  line `limitation shall be deemed to be extended accordingly:]`
  line `1 [Provided also that where a proceeding before the Settlement Commission abates under`
  line `section 245HA, the period of limitation available under this section to the Assessing Officer for making`
  line `an order of assessment or reassessment, as the case may be, shall, after the exclusion of the period under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 245HA, be not less than one year; and where such period of limitation is less`
  line `than one year, it shall be deemed to have been extended to one year.]`
  line `153C.Assessment of income of any other person. — 2 [( 1 )] 3 [Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in section 139, section 147, section 148, section 149, section 151 and section 153, where the Assessing`
  line `Officer is satisfied that, —`
  line `( a ) any money, bullion, jewellery or other valuable article or thing, seized or requisitioned,`
  line `belongs to; or`
  line `( b ) any books of account or documents, seized or requisitioned, pertains or pertain to, or any`
  line `information contained therein, relates to,`
  line `a person other than the person referred to in section 153A, then, the books of account or documents or`
  line `assets, seized or requisitioned shall be handed over to the Assessing Officer having jurisdiction over such`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 61 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `2. Section 153C renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 18 of 2005, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 37, for certain words and figures (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_596_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_597:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-597
  sectionNo (597)
  orderNo 597
  title `Page 597`
  content obj_root_law_sections_597_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_597_footnotes
  sourcePage 597
obj_root_law_sections_597_content:
  string
  line 597
  line `other person] 1 [and that Assessing Officer shall proceed against each such other person and issue notice`
  line `and assess or reassess the income of the other person in accordance with the provisions of section 153A,`
  line `if, that Assessing Officer is satisfied that the books of account or documents or assets seized or`
  line `requisitioned have a bearing on the determination of the total income of such other person 2 [ for six`
  line `assessment years immediately preceding the assessment year relevant to the previous year in which`
  line `search is conducted or requisition is made and ] for the relevant assessment year or years referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 153A]:]`
  line `3 [ Provided that in case of such other person, the reference to the date of initiation of the search`
  line `under section 132 or making of requisition under section 132A in the second proviso to`
  line `4 [sub-section ( 1 ) of section 153A] shall be construed as reference to the date of receiving the books of`
  line `account or documents or assets seized or requisitioned by the Assessing Officer having jurisdiction over`
  line `such other person:]`
  line `5 [ Provided further that the Central Government may by rulesmade by it and published in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify the class or classes of cases in respect of such other person, in which the Assessing`
  line `Officer shall not be required to issue notice for assessing or reassessing the total income for six`
  line `assessment years immediately preceding the assessment year relevant to the previous year in which`
  line `search is conducted or requisition is made 2 [ and for the relevant assessment year or years as referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 153A ] except in cases where any assessment or reassessment has abated.]`
  line `3 [( 2 ) Where books of account or documents or assets seized or requisitioned as referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) has or have been received by the Assessing Officer having jurisdiction over such other`
  line `person after the due date for furnishing the return of income for the assessment year relevant to the`
  line `previous year in which search is conducted under section 132 or requisition is made under section 132A`
  line `and in respect of such assessment year —`
  line `( a ) no return of income has been furnished by such other person and no notice under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142 has been issued to him, or`
  line `( b ) a return of income has been furnished by such other person but no notice under`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 143 has been served and limitation of serving the notice under`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 143 has expired, or`
  line `( c ) assessment or reassessment, if any, has been made,`
  line `before the date of receiving the books of account or documents or assets seized or requisitioned by the`
  line `Assessing Officer having jurisdiction over such other person, such Assessing Officer shall issue the notice`
  line `and assess or reassess total income of such other person of such assessment year in the manner provided`
  line `in section 153A.]`
  line `6 [ 153D. Prior approval necessary for assessment in cases of search or requisition. — No order of`
  line `assessment or reassessment shall be passed by an Assessing Officer below the rank of Joint`
  line `Commissioner in respect of each assessment year referred to in clause ( b ) of`
  line `7 [sub-section ( 1 ) of section 153A] or the assessment year referred to in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 153B, except with the prior approval of the Joint Commissioner:]`
  line `8 [Provided that nothing contained in this section shall apply where the assessment or reassessment`
  line `order, as the case may be, is required to be passed by the Assessing Officer with the prior approval of the`
  line `9 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] under sub-section ( 12 )of section 144BA.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 55, for “and that Assessing Officer shall proceed against each such other person and issue`
  line `such other person notice and assess or reassess income of such other person in accordance with the provisons of section`
  line `153A” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2014).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 62 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line `4. Subs. by 18 of 2008, s. 38, for “section 153A” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2003).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 69 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 39, for “section 153A” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2007).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 43 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_597_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_598:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-598
  sectionNo (598)
  orderNo 598
  title `Page 598`
  content obj_root_law_sections_598_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_598_footnotes
  sourcePage 598
obj_root_law_sections_598_content:
  string
  line 598
  line `154. Rectification of mistake. — 1 [( 1 ) With a view to rectifying any mistake apparent from the record`
  line `an income-tax authority referred to in section 116 may, —`
  line `( a ) amend any order passed by it under the provisions of this Act;`
  line `2 [( b ) amend any intimation or deemed intimation under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143;]]`
  line `3 [( c ) amend any intimation under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 200A;]`
  line `4 [( d ) amend any intimation under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 206CB.]`
  line `5 [( 1A ) Where any matter has been considered and decided in any proceeding by way of appeal or`
  line `revision relating to an order referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), the authority passing such order may,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force, amend the order under that`
  line `sub-section in relation to any matter other than the matter which has been so considered and decided.]`
  line `( 2 ) Subject to the other provisions of this section, the authority concerned —`
  line `( a ) may make an amendment under sub-section ( 1 ) of its own motion, and`
  line `( b ) shall make such amendment for rectifying any such mistake which has been brought to its`
  line `notice 6 [by the assessee or by the deductor,] 4 [or by the collector], and where the authority concerned`
  line `is the 7 [ 8 *** Commissioner (Appeals)], by the 9 [Assessing Officer] also.`
  line `10 * * * * *`
  line `( 3 ) An amendment, which has the effect of enhancing an assessment or reducing a refund or`
  line `otherwise increasing the liability of 11 [the assessee or the deductor] 4 [or the collector], shall not be made`
  line `under this section unless the authority concerned has given notice to 11 [the assessee or the deductor] 4 [or`
  line `the collector] of its intention so to do and has allowed 11 [the assessee or the deductor] 4 [or the collector] a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line `( 4 ) Where an amendment is made under this section, an order shall be passed in writing by the`
  line `income-tax authority concerned.`
  line `12 [( 5 ) Where any such amendment has the effect of reducing the assessment or otherwise reducing the`
  line `liability of the assessee or the deductor 4 [or the collector], the Assessing Officer shall make any refund`
  line `which may be due to such assessee or the deductor 4 [or the collector].]`
  line `( 6 ) Where any such amendment has the effect of enhancing the assessment or reducing a refund`
  line `13 [already made or otherwise increasing the liability of the assessee or the deductor 4 [or the collector], the`
  line `Assessing Officer shall serve on the assessee or the deductor 4 [or the collector], as the case may be] a`
  line `notice of demand in the prescribed form specifying the sum payable, and such notice of demand shall be`
  line `deemed to be issued under section 156 and the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly.`
  line `( 7 ) Save as otherwise provided in section 155 or sub-section ( 4 ) of section 186 no amendment under`
  line `this section shall be made after the expiry of four years 14 [from the end of the financial year in which the`
  line `order sought to be amended was passed].`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 60, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 65, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 70(w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 38 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 31 of 1964, s. 7 (w.e.f. 6-10-1964).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 70, for “by the assessee” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `8. The words “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or the” omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998). Earlier the`
  line `quoted words subs tituted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `10. Omitted by Act 32 of 1994, s. 38 (w.e.f. 1-6-1994). Earlier the proviso inserted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 61 (w.e.f. 14-5-`
  line `1992).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 70, for “the assessee” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
  line `12. Subs. by s. 70, ibid., for sub-section ( 5 ) (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `13. Subs. by s. 70, ibid., for “already made, the Assessing Officer shall serve on the assessee” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
  line `14. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 29, for “from the date of the order sought to be amended” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1984).`
