  line 599
  line `1 [( 8 ) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section ( 7 ), where an application for amendment`
  line `under this section is made 2 [by the assessee or by the deductor] 3 [or by the collector] on or after the 1st`
  line `day of June, 2001 to an income-tax authority referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), the authority shall pass an`
  line `order, within a period of six months from the end of the month in which the application is received by`
  line `it, —`
  line `( a ) making the amendment; or`
  line `( b ) refusing to allow the claim.]`
  line `155. Other amendments. — ( 1 ) 4 [Where, in respect of any completed assessment of a partner in a`
  line `firm for the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1992, or any earlier assessment year,] it`
  line `is found —`
  line `( a ) on the assessment or reassessment of the firm, or`
  line `( b ) on any reduction or enhancement made in the income of the firm under this section, section`
  line `154, section 250, section 254, section 260, section 262, section 263 or section 264, 5 [or]`
  line `5 [( c ) on any order passed under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 245D on the application made by the`
  line firm,]
  line `that the share of the partner in the income of the firm has not been included in the assessment of the`
  line `partner or, if included, is not correct, the 6 [Assessing Officer] may amend the order of assessment of the`
  line `partner with a view to the inclusion of the share in the assessment or the correction thereof, as the case`
  line `may be; and the provisions of section 154 shall, so far as may be, apply thereto, the period of four years`
  line `specified in sub-section ( 7 ) of that section being reckoned 7 [from the end of the financial year in which`
  line `the final order was passed] in the case of the firm.`
  line `8 [( 1A ) Where in respect of any completed assessment of a firm it is found —`
  line `( a ) on the assessment or reassessment of the firm, or`
  line `( b ) on any reduction or enhancement made in the income of the firm under this section, section`
  line `154, section 250, section 254, section 260, section 262, section 263 or section 264, or`
  line `( c ) on any order passed under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 245D on the application made by the`
  line firm,
  line `that any remuneration to any partner is not deductible under clause ( b ) of section 40, the Assessing`
  line `Officer may amend the order of assessment of the partner with a view to adjusting the income of the`
  line `partner to the extent of the amount not so deductible; and the provisions of section 154 shall, so far as`
  line `may be, apply thereto, the period of four years specified in sub-section ( 7 ) of that section being reckoned`
  line `from the end of the financial year in which the final order was passed in the case of the firm.]`
  line `( 2 ) Where in respect of any completed assessment of a member of an association of persons or of a`
  line `body of individuals it is found —`
  line `( a ) on the assessment or reassessment of the association or body, or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1-6-2001).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 70, for “by the assessee” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 38 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 62, for “Where in respect of any completed assessment of a partner in a firm” (w.e.f. 1 -4-`
  line `1993). Earlier the quoted words were restoredby Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989) and substituted by Act 4 of 1988,`
  line `s. 61 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 30, for “from the date of the final order passed” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1984).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 62 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
