  line 601
  line `( iii ) for any other purpose which is not a purpose of the business of the undertaking,`
  line `the investment allowance originally allowed shall be deemed to have been wrongly allowed, and the`
  line `1 [Assessing Officer] may, notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, recompute the total income of`
  line `the assessee for the relevant previous year and make the necessary amendment; and the provisions`
  line `of section 154 shall, so far as may be, apply thereto, the period of four years specified in sub-section ( 7 )`
  line `of that section being reckoned, —`
  line `( i ) in a case referred to in clause ( a ), from the end of the previous year in which the sale or other`
  line `transfer took place;`
  line `( ii ) in a case referred to in clause ( b ), from the end of the ten years referred to in that clause;`
  line `( iii ) in a case referred to in clause ( c ), from the end of the previous year in which the amount was`
  line utilised.
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of clause ( b ), “new ship” or “new aircraft” or “new machinery or`
  line `plant” shall have the same meanings as in the 2 [ Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 32A].]`
  line `( 5 ) Where an allowance by way of development rebate has been made wholly or partly to an assessee`
  line `in respect of a ship, machinery or plant installed after the 31st day of December, 1957, in any assessment`
  line `year under section 33 or under the corresponding provisions of the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of`
  line `1922), and subsequently —`
  line `( i ) at any time before the expiry of eight years from the end of the previous year in which the ship`
  line `was acquired or the machinery or plant was installed, the ship, machinery or plant is sold or otherwise`
  line `transferred by the assessee to any person other than the Government, a local authority, a corporation`
  line `established by a Central, State or Provincial Act or a Government company as defined in section 617`
  line `of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or in connection with any amalgamation or succession`
  line `referred to in sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 4 ) of section 33; or`
  line `( ii ) at any time before the expiry of the eight years referred to in sub-section ( 3 ) of section 34, the`
  line `assesseeutilises the amount credited to the reserve account under clause ( a ) of that sub-section —`
  line `( a ) for distribution by way of dividends or profits; or`
  line `( b ) for remittance outside India as profits or for the creation of any asset outside India; or`
  line `( c ) for any other purpose which is not a purpose of the business of the undertaking,`
  line `the development rebate originally allowed shall be deemed to have been wrongly allowed, and the`
  line `1 [Assessing Officer] may, notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, recompute the total income of`
  line `the assessee for the relevant previous year and make the necessary amendment; and the provisions`
  line `of section 154 shall, so far as may be, apply thereto, the period of four years specified in sub-section ( 7 )`
  line `of that section being reckoned from the end of the previous year in which the sale or transfer took place or`
  line `the money was so utilised.`
  line `3 [( 5A ) Where an allowance by way of development allowance has been made wholly or partly to an`
  line `assessee in respect of the cost of planting in any area in any assessment year under section 33A and`
  line `subsequently —`
  line `( i ) at any time before the expiry of eight years from the end of the previous year in which such`
  line `allowance was made, the land is sold or otherwise transferred by the assessee to any person other than`
  line `the Government, a local authority, a corporation established by a Central, State or Provincial Act or a`
  line `Government company as defined in section 617 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or in`
  line `connection with any amalgamation or succession referred to in sub-section ( 5 ) or sub-section ( 6 ) of`
  line `section 33A; or`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 32, for “ Explanation to clause ( vi ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 32” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 39 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
