obj_root_law_sections_603_content:
  string
  line 603
  line `at any time before the expiry of the period of eight years from the date of such transfer, the Assessing`
  line `Officer may, notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, recompute the total income of the transferor`
  line `company for the relevant previous year and make the necessary amendment; and the provisions of section`
  line `154 shall, so far as may be, apply thereto, the period of four years specified in sub-section ( 7 ) of that`
  line `section being reckoned from the end of the previous year in which the capital asset was so converted or`
  line `treated or in which the parent company or its nominees or, as the case may be, the holding company`
  line `ceased to hold the whole of the share capital of the subsidiary company.]`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `2 [( 10A ) Where in the assessment for any year, a capital gain arising from the transfer of a 3 [long-term`
  line `capital asset], is charged to tax and within a period of six months after the date of such transfer, the`
  line `assessee has made any investment or deposit in any specified asset within the meaning of Explanation`
  line `1 to sub-section ( 1 ) of section 54E, the 4 [Assessing Officer] shall amend the order of assessment so as to`
  line `exclude the amount of the capital gain not chargeable to tax 5 [under the provisions of sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 54E]; and the provisions of section 154 shall, so far as may be, apply thereto, the period of four`
  line `years specified in sub-section ( 7 ) of that section being 6 [reckoned from the end of the financial year in`
  line `which the assessment was made].]`
  line `7 * * * * *`
  line `8 [( 11 ) Where in the assessment for any year, a capital gain arising from the transfer of any original`
  line `asset as is referred to in section 54H is charged to tax and within the period extended under that section`
  line `the assessee acquires the new asset referred to in that section or, as the case may be, deposits or invests`
  line `the amount of such capital gain within the period so extended, the Assessing Officer shall amend the`
  line `order of assessment so as to exclude the amount of the capital gain not chargeable to tax under any of the`
  line `sections referred to in section 54H; and the provisions of section 154 shall, so far as may be, apply`
  line `thereto, the period of four years specified in sub-section (7) of section 154 being reckoned from the end of`
  line `the previous year in which the compensation was received by the assessee.`
  line `9 [( 11A ) Where in the assessment for any year, the deduction under section 10A or section`
  line `10B or section 10BA has not been allowed on the ground that such income has not been received in`
  line `convertible foreign exchange in India, or having been received in convertible foreign exchange outside`
  line `India, or having been converted into convertible foreign exchange outside India, has not been brought into`
  line `India, by or on behalf of the assessee with the approval of the Reserve Bank of India or such other`
  line `authority as is authorised under any law for the time being in force for regulating payments and dealings`
  line `in foreign exchange and subsequently such income or part thereof has been or is received in, or brought`
  line `into, India in the manner aforesaid, the Assessing Officer shall amend the order of assessment so as to`
  line `allow deduction under section 10A or section 10B or section 10BA, as the case may be, in respect of such`
  line `income or part thereof as is so received in, or brought into, India, and the provisions of section 154 shall,`
  line `so far as may be, apply thereto, and the period of four years shall be reckoned from the end of the`
  line `previous year in which such income is so received in, or brought into, India.]`
  line `( 12 ) Where in the assessment for any year commencing before the 1st day of April, 1988, the`
  line `deduction under section 80-O in respect of any income, being the whole or any part of income by way of`
  line `royalty, commission, fees or any similar payment as is referred to in that section, has not been allowed on`
  line `the ground that such income has not been received in convertible foreign exchange in India, or having`
  line `been received in convertible foreign exchange outside India, or having been converted into convertible`
  line `1. Sub-sections ( 8 ), ( 8A ), ( 9 ), ( 9A ) and ( 10 ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 61 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-1978).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 74, for “capital asset, not being a short - term capital asset” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 19 of 1978, s. 19, for “under the provisions of section 54E” (w.r.e.f. 1 -4-1974).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 30, for “reckoned from the date of the assessment” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1984).`
  line `7. Sub-section ( 10B ) and ( 10C ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 61 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 48 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991). Sub-section ( 11 ) was omitted by Act 32 of 1985, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-4-1986)`
  line `and sub-section ( 12 ) was omitted by Act 11 of 1987, s. 44 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988) which were earlier inserted by Act 20 of`
  line `1974, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 14 (w.e.f. 13-7-2006).`
