obj_root_law_sections_604_content:
  string
  line 604
  line `foreign exchange outside India, has not been brought into India, by or on behalf of the assessee in`
  line `accordance with any law for the time being in force for regulating payments and dealings in foreign`
  line `exchange and subsequently such income or part thereof has been or is received in, or brought into, India`
  line `in the manner aforesaid, the Assessing Officer shall amend the order of assessment so as to allow`
  line `deduction under section 80-O in respect of such income or part thereof as is so received in, or brought`
  line `into, India; and the provisions of section 154 shall, so far as may be, apply thereto, the period of four`
  line `years specified in sub-section (7) of that section being reckoned from the end of the previous year in`
  line `which such income is so received in, or brought into, India; so, however, that the period from the 1st day`
  line `of April, 1988 to the 30th day of September, 1991 shall be excluded in computing the period of four`
  line years.]
  line `1 [( 13 ) Where in the assessment for any year, the deduction under section 80HHB or section`
  line `80HHC or section 80HHD or section 80HHE or section 80-O or section 80R or section 80RR or section`
  line `80RRA has not been allowed on the ground that such income has not been received in convertible foreign`
  line `exchange in India, or having been received in convertible foreign exchange outside India, or having been`
  line `converted into convertible foreign exchange outside India, has not been brought into India, by or on`
  line `behalf of the assessee with the approval of the Reserve Bank of India or such other authority as is`
  line `authorised under any law for the time being in force for regulating payments and dealings in foreign`
  line `exchange and subsequently such income or part thereof has been or is received in, or brought into, India`
  line `in the manner aforesaid, the Assessing Officer shall amend the order of assessment so as to allow`
  line `deduction under section 80HHB or section 80HHC or section 80HHD or section 80HHE or`
  line `section 80-O or section 80R or section 80RR or section 80RRA, as the case may be, in respect of such`
  line `income or part thereof as is so received in, or brought into, India; and the provisions of section 154 shall,`
  line `so far as may be, apply thereto, and the period of four years shall be reckoned from the end of the`
  line `previous year in which such income is so received in, or brought into, India.`
  line `2 [( 14 ) Where in the assessment for any previous year or in any intimation or deemed intimation under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143 for any previous year, 3 [credit for tax deducted or collected in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of section 199 or, as the case may be, section 206C] has not been given on the ground`
  line `that the certificate furnished under 4 [section 203 or section 206C] was not filed with the return and`
  line `subsequently such certificate is produced before the Assessing Officer within two years from the end of`
  line `the assessment year in which such income is assessable, the Assessing Officer shall amend the order of`
  line `assessment or any intimation or deemed intimation under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143, as the case may`
  line `be, and the provisions of section 154 shall, so far as may be, apply thereto:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply unless the 5 [income from which the tax`
  line `has been deducted or income on which the tax has been collected] has been disclosed in the return of`
  line `income filed by the assessee for the relevant assessment year.`
  line `6 [( 14A ) Where in the assessment for any previous year or in any intimation or deemed intimation`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143 for any previous year, credit for income-tax paid in any country`
  line `outside India or a specified terriotory outside India referred to in section 90, section 90A or section 91 has`
  line `not been given on the ground that the payment of such tax was under dispute, and if subsequently such`
  line `dispute is settled, and the assessee, within six months from the end of the month in which the dispute is`
  line `settled, furnishes to the Assessing Officer evidence of settlement of dispute and evidence of payment of`
  line `such tax along with an undertaking that no credit in respect of such amount has directly or indirectly been`
  line `claimed or shall be claimed for any other assessment year, the Assessing Officer shall amend the order of`
  line `assessment or any intimation or deemed intimation under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143, as the case may`
  line `be, and the provisions of section 154 shall, so far as may be, apply thereto:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 66 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999). Sub-section ( 13 ) was omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 61 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989)`
  line `which was inserted by Act 25 of 1975, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-1975).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 62 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 39, for “credit for tax deducted in accordance with the provisions of section 199”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 39, ibid., for “section 203” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2007).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 39, for “income from which the tax has been deducted” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2007).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 63 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
