obj_root_law_sections_605_content:
  string
  line 605
  line `Provided that the credit of tax which was under dispute shall be allowed for the year in which such`
  line `income is offered to tax or assessed to tax in India:]`
  line `( 15 ) Where in the assessment for any year, a capital gain arising from the transfer of a capital asset,`
  line `being land or building or both, is computed by taking the full value of the consideration received or`
  line `accruing as a result of the transfer to be the value adopted or assessed by any authority of a State`
  line `Government for the purpose of payment of stamp duty in accordance with sub-section ( 1 ) of section 50C,`
  line `and subsequently such value is revised in any appeal or revision or reference referred to in clause ( b ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of that section, the Assessing Officer shall amend the order of assessment so as to`
  line `compute the capital gain by taking the full value of the consideration to be the value as so revised in such`
  line `appeal or revision or reference; and the provisions of section 154 shall, so far as may be, apply thereto,`
  line `and the period of four years shall be reckoned from the end of the previous year in which the order`
  line `revising the value was passed in that appeal or revision or reference.]`
  line `1 [( 16 ) Where in the assessment for any year, a capital gain arising from the transfer of a capital asset,`
  line `being a transfer by way of compulsory acquisition under any law, or a transfer, the consideration for`
  line `which was determined or approved by the Central Government or the Reserve Bank of India, is computed`
  line `by taking the compensation or consideration as referred to in clause ( a ) or, as the case may be, the`
  line `compensation or consideration enhanced or further enhanced as referred to in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 5 )`
  line `of section 45, to be the full value of consideration deemed to be received or accruing as a result of the`
  line `transfer of the asset and subsequently such compensation or consideration is reduced by any court,`
  line `Tribunal or other authority, the Assessing Officer shall amend the order of assessment so as to compute`
  line `the capital gain by taking the compensation or consideration as so reduced by the court, Tribunal or any`
  line `other authority to be the full value of consideration; and the provisions of section 154 shall, so far as may`
  line `be, apply thereto, and the period of four years shall be reckoned from the end of the previous year in`
  line `which the order reducing the compensation was passed by the court, Tribunal or other authority.`
  line `( 17 ) Where a deduction has been allowed to an assessee in any assessment year under section 80RRB`
  line `in respect of any patent, and subsequently by an order of the Controller or the High Court under the`
  line `Patents Act, 1970 (39 of 1970), —`
  line `( i ) the patent was revoked, or`
  line `( ii ) the name of the assessee was excluded from the patents register as patentee in respect of that`
  line patent,
  line `the deduction from the income by way of royalty attributable to the period during which the patent had`
  line `been revoked or the period for which the assessee’s name was excluded as patentee in respect of that`
  line `patent, shall be deemed to have been wrongly allowed and the Assessing Officer may, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act, recompute the total income of the assessee for the relevant previous year`
  line `and make necessary amendment; and the provisions of section 154 shall, so far as may be, apply thereto,`
  line `the period of four years specified in sub-section ( 7 ) of that section being reckoned from the end of the`
  line `previous year in which such order of the Controller referred to in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ), or the High`
  line `Court referred to in clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 2, of the Patents Act, 1970 (39 of 1970), as the`
  line `case may be, was passed.]`
  line `2 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “additional compensation” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( 1 ) of`
  line `the Explanation to sub-section ( 2 ) of section 54;`
  line `( b ) “additional consideration”, in relation to the transfer of any capital asset the consideration for`
  line `which was determined or approved by the Central Government or the Reserve Bank of India, means`
  line `the difference between the amount of consideration for such transfer as enhanced by any court,`
  line `tribunal or other authority and the amount of consideration which would have been payable if such`
  line `enhancement had not been made.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 66 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 19 of 1978, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
