obj_root_law_sections_606_content:
  string
  line 606
  line `156. Notice of demand. — When any tax, interest, penalty, fine or any other sum 1 *** is payable in`
  line `consequence of any order passed under this Act, the 2 [Assessing Officer] shall serve upon the assessee a`
  line `notice of demand in the prescribed formspecifying the sum so payable:`
  line `3 [Provided that where any sum is determined to be payable by the assessee or 4 [the deductor or the`
  line `collector under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143 or sub-section ( 1 ) of section 200A or sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 206CB], the intimation under those sub-sections shall be deemed to be a notice of demand for`
  line `the purposes of this section.]`
  line `157. Intimation of loss. — When, in the course of the assessment of the total income of any assessee,`
  line `it is established that a loss has taken place which the assessee is entitled to have carried forward and set`
  line `off under the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 72, sub-section ( 2 ) of section 73, 5 [ 6 [sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `or sub-section ( 3 ) of section 74] or sub-section ( 3 ) of section 74A], the 2 [Assessing Officer] shall notify to`
  line `the assessee by an order in writing the amount of the loss as computed by him for the purposes of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 72, sub-section ( 2 ) of section 73, 5 [ 6 [sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 3 ) of`
  line `section 74 ] or sub-section ( 3 ) of section 74A].`
  line `158. Intimation of assessment of firm. — 7 [Whenever, in respect of the assessment year commencing`
  line `on the 1st day of April, 1992, or any earlier assessment year, a registered firm is assessed], or an`
  line `unregistered firm is assessed under the provisions of clause ( b ) of section 183, the 2 [Assessing Officer]`
  line `shall notify to the firm by an order in writing the amount of its total income assessed and the`
  line `apportionment thereof between the several partners.`
  line `8 [CHAPTER XIVA`
  line `S PECIAL PROVISION FOR AVOIDING REPETITIVE APPEALS`
  line `158A. Procedure when assessee claims identical question of law is pending before High Court or`
  line `Supreme Court. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, where an assessee claims that any`
  line `question of law arising in his case for an assessment year which is pending before the 2 [Assessing`
  line `Officer] or any appellate authority (such case being hereafter in this section referred to as the relevant`
  line `case) is identical with a question of law arising in his case for another assessment year which is pending`
  line `before the High Court on a reference under section 256 or 9 [before the Supreme Court on a reference`
  line `under section 257 or in appeal under section 260A before the High Court or in appeal under`
  line `section 261 before the Supreme Court] (such case being hereafter in this section referred to as the other`
  line `case), he may furnish to the 2 [Assessing Officer] or the appellate authority, as the case may be, a`
  line `declaration in the prescribed form and verifiedin the prescribed manner, that if the 2 [Assessing Officer] or`
  line `the appellate authority, as the case may be, agrees to apply in the relevant case the final decision on the`
  line `question of law in the other case, he shall not raise such question of law in the relevant case in appeal`
  line `before any appellate authority or 10 [in appeal before the High Court under section 260A or in appeal`
  line `before the Supreme Court under section 261].`
  line `1. The brackets, words, figures and letter “(including annuity deposit referred to in Chapter XXII - A)” omitted by Act 13 of`
  line `1966, s. 32 and The Third Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-1967).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 71, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 39, for “by the d eductor under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143 or sub-section ( 1 ) of section`
  line `200A” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2015).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 20 of 1974, s. 13, for “or sub -section ( 1 ) of section 74” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1975).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 74, for “sub -section ( 1 ) of sect ion 74” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 63, for “Whenever a registered firm is assessed” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1993).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 63, for “before the Supreme Court on a referen ce under section 257 or in appeal under section`
  line `261” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2002).`
  line `10. Subs. by s. 63, ibid., for “for a reference before the High Court under section 256 or the Supreme Court under section`
  line `257 or in appeal before the Supreme Court under section 261” (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
