obj_root_law_sections_607_content:
  string
  line 607
  line `( 2 ) Where a declaration under sub-section ( 1 ) is furnished to any appellate authority, the appellate`
  line `authority shall call for a report from the 1 [Assessing Officer] on the correctness of the claim made by the`
  line `assessee and, where the 1 [Assessing Officer] makes a request to the appellate authority to give him an`
  line `opportunity of being heard in the matter, the appellate authority shall allow him such opportunity.`
  line `( 3 ) The 1 [Assessing Officer] or the appellate authority, as the case may be, may, by order in`
  line `writing, —`
  line `( i ) admit the claim of the assessee if he or it is satisfied that the question of law arising in the`
  line `relevant case is identical with the question of law in the other case; or`
  line `( ii ) reject the claim if he or it is not so satisfied.`
  line `( 4 ) Where a claim is admitted under sub-section ( 3 ), —`
  line `( a ) the 1 [Assessing Officer] or, as the case may be, the appellate authority may make an order`
  line `disposing of the relevant case without awaiting the final decision on the question of law in the other`
  line `case; and`
  line `( b ) the assessee shall not be entitled to raise, in relation to the relevant case, such question of law`
  line `in appeal before any appellate authority or 2 [in appeal before the High Court under section 260A or`
  line `the Supreme Court undersection 261].`
  line `( 5 ) When the decision on the question of law in the other case becomes final, it shall be applied to the`
  line `relevant case and the 1 [Assessing Officer] or the appellate authority, as the case may be, shall, if`
  line `necessary, amend the order referred to in clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 4 ) conformably to such decision.`
  line `( 6 ) An order under sub-section ( 3 ) shall be final and shall not be called in question in any proceeding`
  line `by way of appeal, reference or revision under this Act.`
  line `Explanation. — In this section, —`
  line `( a ) “appellate authority” means the 3 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)], the Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals) or the Appellate Tribunal;`
  line `( b ) ”case”, in relation to an assessee, means any proceeding under this Act for the assessment of`
  line `the total income of the assessee or for the imposition of any penalty or fine on him.]`
  line `4 [ 158AA. Procedure when in an appeal by revenue an identical question of law is pending`
  line `before Supreme Court. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, where the Commissioner`
  line `or Principal Commissioner is of the opinion that any question of law arising in the case of an assessee for`
  line `any assessment year (such case being herein referred to as relevant case) is identical with a question of`
  line `law arising in his case for another assessment year which is pending before the Supreme Court, in an`
  line `appeal under section 261 or in a special leave petition under article 136 of the Constitution, against the`
  line `order of the High Court in favour of the assessee (such case being herein referred to as the other case), he`
  line `may, instead of directing the Assessing Officer to appeal to the Appellate Tribunal under sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `or sub-section ( 2A ) of section 253, direct the Assessing Officer to make an application to the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal in the prescribed form within sixty days from the date of receipt of the order of the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals) stating that an appeal on the question of law arising in the relevant case may be`
  line `filed when the decision on the question of law becomes final in the other case.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 63, for “for a reference before the High Court under section 256 or the Supreme Court under`
  line `section 257 or in appeal before the S upreme Court under section 261” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2002).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_607_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_608:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-608
