  content obj_root_law_sections_608_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_608_footnotes
  sourcePage 608
obj_root_law_sections_608_content:
  string
  line 608
  line `( 2 ) The Commissioner or Principal Commissioner shall direct the Assessing Officer to make an`
  line `application under sub-section ( 1 ) only if an acceptance is received from the assessee to the effect that the`
  line `question of law in the other case is identical to that arising in the relevant case; and in case no such`
  line `acceptance is received, the Commissioner or Principal Commissioner shall proceed in accordance with`
  line `the provisions contained in sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-section ( 2A ) of section 253.`
  line `( 3 ) Where the order of the Commissioner (Appeals) referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) is not in conformity`
  line `with the final decision on the question of law in the other case, the Commissioner or Principal`
  line `Commissioner may direct the Assessing Officer to appeal to the Appellate Tribunal against such order`
  line `and save as otherwise provided in this section all other provisions of Part B of Chapter XX shall apply`
  line accordingly.
  line `( 4 ) Every appeal under sub-section ( 3 ) shall be filed within sixty days from the date on which the`
  line `order of the Supreme Court in the other case is communicated to the Commissioner or Principal`
  line Commissioner.]
  line `1 [CHAPTER XIVB`
  line `S PECIAL PROCEDURE FOR ASSESSMENT OF SEARCH CASES`
  line `158B.Definitions. — In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `2 [( a ) “block period” means the period comprising previous years relevant to six assessment years`
  line `preceding the previous year in which the search was conducted under section 132 or any requisition`
  line `was made under section 132A and also includes the period up to the date of the commencement of`
  line `such search or date of such requisition in the previous year in which the said search was conducted or`
  line `requisition was made:`
  line `Provided that where the search is initiated or the requisition is made before the 1st day of June,`
  line `2001, the provisions of this clause shall have effect as if for the words “six assessment years”, the`
  line `words “ten assessment years” had been substituted;]`
  line `( b ) “undisclosed income” includes any money, bullion, jewellery or other valuable article or`
  line `thing or any income based on any entry in the books of account or other documents or transactions,`
  line `where such money, bullion, jewellery, valuable article, thing, entry in the books of account or other`
  line `document or transaction represents wholly or partly income or property which has not been or would`
  line `not have been disclosed for the purposes of this Act 3 [, or any expense, deduction or allowance`
  line `claimed under this Act which is found to be false].`
  line `158BA. Assessment of undisclosed income as a result of search. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other provisions of this Act, where after the 30th day of June, 1995 a search is initiated`
  line `under section 132 or books of account, other documents or any assets are requisitioned under section`
  line `132A in the case of any person, then, the Assessing Officer shall proceed to assess the undisclosed`
  line `income in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line `( 2 ) The total undisclosed income relating to the block period shall be charged to tax, at the rate`
  line `specified in section 113, as income of the block period irrespective of the previous year or years to which`
  line `such income relates and irrespective of the fact whether regular assessment for any one or more of the`
  line `relevant assessment years is pending or not.`
  line `4 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that —`
  line `( a ) the assessment made under this Chapter shall be in addition to the regular assessment in`
  line `respect of each previous year included in the block period;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-7-1995).`
  line `2. Subs. by 14 of 2001, s. 66, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2001).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 64 (w.e.f. 1-7-1995).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 44 (w.e.f. 1-7-1995).`
obj_root_law_sections_608_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_609:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-609
  sectionNo (609)
  orderNo 609
  title `Page 609`
  content obj_root_law_sections_609_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_609_footnotes
  sourcePage 609
obj_root_law_sections_609_content:
  string
  line 609
  line `( b ) the total undisclosed income relating to the block period shall not include the income assessed`
  line `in any regular assessment as income of such block period;`
  line `( c ) the income assessed in this Chapter shall not be included in the regular assessment of any`
  line `previous year included in the block period.]`
  line `( 3 ) Where the assessee proves to the satisfaction of the Assessing Officer that any part of income`
  line `referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) relates to an assessment year for which the previous year has not ended or`
  line `the date of filing the return of income under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139 for any previous year has not`
  line `expired, and such income or the transactions relating to such income are recorded on or before the date of`
  line `the search or requisition in the books of account or other documents maintained in the normal course`
  line `relating to such previous years, the said income shall not be included in the block period.`
  line `158BB. Computation of undisclosed income of the block period. — ( 1 ) The undisclosed income of`
  line `the block period shall be the aggregate of the total income of the previous years falling within the block`
  line `period computed, 1 [in accordance with the provisions of this Act, on the basis of evidence found as a`
  line `result of search or requisition of books of account or other documents and such other materials or`
  line `information as are available with the Assessing Officer and relatable to such evidence], as reduced by the`
  line `aggregate of the total income, or as the case may be, as increased by the aggregate of the losses of such`
  line `previous years, determined, —`
  line `( a ) where assessments under section 143 or section 144 or section 147 2 [have been concluded`
  line `prior to the date of commencement of the search or the date of requisition], on the basis of such`
  line assessments;
  line `( b ) where returns of income have been filed under section 139 3 [or in response to a notice issued`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142 or section 148] but assessments have not been made till the date`
  line `of search or requisition, on the basis of the income disclosed in such returns;`
  line `4 [( c ) where the due date for filing a return of income has expired, but no return of income has`
  line `been filed, —`
  line `( A ) on the basis of entries as recorded in the books of account and other documents`
  line `maintained in the normal course on or before the date of the search or requisition where such`
  line `entries result in computation of loss for any previous year falling in the block period; or`
  line `( B ) on the basis of entries as recorded in the books of account and other documents`
  line `maintained in the normal course on or before the date of the search or requisition where such`
  line `income does not exceed the maximum amount not chargeable to tax for any previous year falling`
  line `in the block period;`
  line `( ca ) where the due date for filing a return of income has expired, but no return of income has`
  line `been filed, as nil, in cases not falling under clause ( c );]`
  line `( d ) where the previous year has not ended or the date of filing the return of income under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139 has not expired, on the basis of entries relating to such income or`
  line `transactions as recorded in the books of account and other documents maintained in the normal`
  line `course on or before the date of the search or requisition relating to such previous years;`
  line `( e ) where any order of settlement has been made under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 245D, on the`
  line `basis of such order;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 65, for certain words and figure (w.e.f. 1-7-1995).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 65, ibid., for “have been concluded” (w.e.f. 1 -7-1995).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 65, ibid., for “or section 147” (w.e.f. 1 -7-1995).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 65, ibid., for clause ( c ) (w.e.f. 1-7-1995).`
