obj_root_law_sections_610_content:
  string
  line 610
  line `( f ) where an assessment of undisclosed income had been made earlier under clause ( c ) of`
  line `section 158BC, on the basis of such assessment.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of determination of undisclosed income, —`
  line `( a ) the total income or loss of each previous year shall, for the purpose of aggregation, be taken`
  line `as the total income or loss computed in accordance with the provisions of 1 [this Act] without giving`
  line `effect to set off of brought forward losses under Chapter VI or unabsorbed depreciation under`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 32:`
  line `2 [Provided that in computing deductions under Chapter VIA for the purposes of the said`
  line `aggregation, effect shall be given to set off of brought forward losses under Chapter VI or unabsorbed`
  line `depreciation under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 32;]`
  line `3 [( b ) of a firm, returned income and total income assessed for each of the previous years falling`
  line `within the block period shall be the income determined before allowing deduction of salary, interest,`
  line `commission, bonus or remuneration by whatever name called 4 [to any partner not being a working`
  line `partner]:`
  line `Provided that undisclosed income of the firm so determined shall not be chargeable to tax in the`
  line `hands of the partners, whether on allocation or on account of enhancement;]`
  line `( c ) assessment under section 143 includes determination of income under sub-section ( 1 ) or`
  line `sub-section ( 1B ) of section 143.`
  line `( 2 ) In computing the undisclosed income of the block period, the provisions of`
  line `sections 68, 69, 69A, 69B and 69C shall, so far as may be, apply and references to “financial year” in`
  line `those sections shall be construed as references to the relevant previous year falling in the block period`
  line `including the previous year ending with the date of search or of the requisition.`
  line `( 3 ) The burden of proving to the satisfaction of the Assessing Officer that any undisclosed income`
  line `had already been disclosed in any return of income filed by the assessee before the commencement of`
  line `search or of the requisition, as the case may be, shall be on the assessee.`
  line `( 4 ) For the purpose of assessment under this Chapter, losses brought forward from the previous year`
  line `under Chapter VI or unabsorbed depreciation under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 32 shall not be set off`
  line `against the undisclosed income determined in the block assessment under this Chapter, but may be carried`
  line `forward for being set off in the regular assessments.`
  line `158BC. Procedure for block assessment. — Where any search has been conducted under`
  line `section 132 or books of account, other documents or assets are requisitioned under section 132A, in the`
  line `case of any person, then, —`
  line `5 [( a ) the Assessing Officer shall —`
  line `( i ) in respect of search initiated or books of account or other documents or any assets`
  line `requisitioned after the 30th day of June, 1995, but before the 1st day of January, 1997, serve a`
  line `notice to such person requiring him to furnish within such time not being less than fifteen days;`
  line `( ii ) in respect of search initiated or books of account or other documents or any assets`
  line `requisitioned on or after the 1st day of January, 1997, serve a notice to such person requiring him`
  line `to furnish within such time not being less than fifteen days but not more than forty-five days,`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 65, for “Chapter IV” (w.e.f. 1 -7-1995).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 65, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-7-1995).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 46, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-7-1995).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 14 of 1997, s. 4, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 1-1-1997).`
