obj_root_law_sections_611_content:
  string
  line 611
  line `as may be specified in the notice a return in the prescribed formand verified in the same manner as a`
  line `return under clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142, setting forth his total income including the`
  line `undisclosed income for the block period:`
  line `Provided that no notice under section 148 is required to be issued for the purpose of proceeding`
  line `under this Chapter:`
  line `Provided further that a person who has furnished a return under this clause shall not be entitled to`
  line `file a revised return;]`
  line `( b ) the Assessing Officer shall proceed to determine the undisclosed income of the block period`
  line `in the manner laid down in section 158BB and the provisions of section 142, sub-sections ( 2 ) and ( 3 )`
  line `of section 143 1 [, section 144 and section 145] shall, so far as may be, apply;`
  line `( c ) the Assessing Officer, on determination of the undisclosed income of the block period in`
  line `accordance with this Chapter, shall pass an order of assessment and determine the tax payable by him`
  line `on the basis of such assessment;`
  line `2 [( d ) the assets seized under section 132 or requisitioned under section 132A shall be dealt with in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of section 132B.]`
  line `158BD. Undisclosed income of any other person. — Where the Assessing Officer is satisfied that`
  line `any undisclosed income belongs to any person, other than the person with respect to whom search was`
  line `made under section 132 or whose books of account or other documents or any assets were requisitioned`
  line `under section 132A, then, the books of account, other documents or assets seized or requisitioned shall be`
  line `handed over to the Assessing Officer having jurisdiction over such other person and that Assessing`
  line `Officer shall proceed 3 [under section 158BC] against such other person and the provisions of this Chapter`
  line `shall apply accordingly.`
  line `158BE. Time limit for completion of block assessment. — 4 [( 1 ) The order under section`
  line `158BC shall be passed —`
  line `( a ) within one year from the end of the month in which the last of the authorisations for search`
  line `under section 132 or for requisition under section 132A, as the case may be, was executed in cases`
  line `where a search is initiated or books of account or other documents or any assets are requisitioned`
  line `after the 30th day of June, 1995, but before the 1st day of January, 1997;`
  line `( b ) within two years from the end of the month in which the last of the authorisations for search`
  line `under section 132 or for requisition under section 132A, as the case may be, was executed in cases`
  line `where a search is initiated or books of account or other documents or any assets are requisitioned on`
  line `or after the 1st day of January, 1997.`
  line `( 2 ) The period of limitation for completion of block assessment in the case of the other person`
  line `referred to in section 158BD shall be —`
  line `( a ) one year from the end of the month in which the notice under this Chapter was served on such`
  line `other person in respect of search initiated or books of account or other documents or any assets`
  line `requisitioned after the 30th day of June, 1995, but before the 1st day of January, 1997; and`
  line `( b ) two years from the end of the month in which the notice under this Chapter was served on`
  line `such other person in respect of search initiated or books of account or other documents or any assets`
  line `are requisitioned on or after the 1st day of January, 1997.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 20 02, s. 66, for “and section 144” (w.e.f. 1 -7-1995).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 66, ibid., for clause ( d ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 67, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 14 of 1997, s. 5, for sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-1-1997).`
