obj_root_law_sections_612_content:
  string
  line 612
  line `1 [ Explanation 1. — In computing the period of limitation for the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) the period during which the assessment proceeding is stayed by an order or injunction of any`
  line `court; or`
  line `( ii ) the period commencing from the day on which the Assessing Officer directs the assessee to`
  line `get his accounts audited under sub-section ( 2A ) of section 142 and ending on the day on which the`
  line `assessee is required to furnish a report of such audit under that sub-section; or`
  line `( iii ) the time taken in reopening the whole or any part of the proceeding or giving an opportunity`
  line `to the assessee to be re-heard under the proviso to section 129; or`
  line `( iv ) in a case where an application made before the Settlement Commission under section 245C is`
  line `rejected by it or is not allowed to be proceeded with by it, the period commencing on the date on`
  line `which such application is made and ending with the date on which the order under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 245D is received by the 2 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] under sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of that section,`
  line `shall be excluded:`
  line `Provided that where immediately after the exclusion of the aforesaid period, the period of limitation`
  line `referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) available to the Assessing Officer for making an order`
  line `under clause ( c ) ofsection 158BC is less than sixty days, such remaining period shall be extended to sixty`
  line `days and the aforesaid period of limitation shall be deemed to be extended accordingly.]`
  line `3 [ Explanation 2. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the authorisation referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to have been executed, —`
  line `( a ) in the case of search, on the conclusion of search as recorded in the last panchnama drawn in`
  line `relation to any person in whose case the warrant of authorisation has been issued;`
  line `( b ) in the case of requisition under section 132A, on the actual receipt of the books of account or`
  line `other documents or assets by the Authorised Officer.]`
  line `158BF. Certain interests and penalties not to be levied or imposed. — No interest under the`
  line `provisions of section 234A, 234B or 234C or penalty under the provisions of clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 271 or section 271A or section 271B shall be levied or imposed upon the assessee in respect of`
  line `the undisclosed income determined in the block assessment.`
  line `4 [ 158BFA. Levy of interest and penalty in certain cases. — ( 1 ) Where the return of total income`
  line `including undisclosed income for the block period, in respect of search initiated under section 132 or`
  line `books of account, other documents or any assets requisitioned under section 132A on or after the 1st day`
  line `of January, 1997, as required by a notice under clause ( a ) of section 158BC, is furnished after the expiry`
  line `of the period specified in such notice, or is not furnished, the assessee shall be liable to pay simple interest`
  line `at the rate of 5 [one per cent.] of the tax on undisclosed income, determined under clause ( c ) of`
  line `section 158BC, for every month or part of a month comprised in the period commencing on the day`
  line `immediately following the expiry of the time specified in the notice, and —`
  line `( a ) where the return is furnished after the expiry of the time aforesaid, ending on the date of`
  line `furnishing the return; or`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 68, for Explanation 1 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 46 (w.e.f. 1-7-1995).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 14 of 1997, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-1-1997).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 7, for “one and one - fourth per cent.” (w.e.f. 8 -9-2003).`
