obj_root_law_sections_613_content:
  string
  line 613
  line `( b ) where no return has been furnished, on the date of completion of assessment under clause ( c )`
  line `of section 158BC.`
  line `( 2 ) The Assessing Officer or the Commissioner (Appeals) in the course of any proceedings under this`
  line `Chapter, may direct that a person shall pay by way of penalty a sum which shall not be less than the`
  line `amount of tax leviable but which shall not exceed three times the amount of tax so leviable in respect of`
  line `the undisclosed income determined by the Assessing Officer under clause ( c ) of section 158BC:`
  line `Provided that no order imposing penalty shall be made in respect of a person if —`
  line `( i ) such person has furnished a return under clause ( a ) of section 158BC;`
  line `( ii ) the tax payable on the basis of such return has been paid or, if the assets seized consist of`
  line `money, the assessee offers the money so seized to be adjusted against the tax payable;`
  line `( iii ) evidence of tax paid is furnished along with the return; and`
  line `( iv ) an appeal is not filed against the assessment of that part of income which is shown in the`
  line `return:`
  line `Provided further that the provisions of the preceding proviso shall not apply where the`
  line `undisclosed income determined by the Assessing Officer is in excess of the income shown in the`
  line `return and in such cases the penalty shall be imposed on that portion of undisclosed income`
  line `determined which is in excess of the amount of undisclosed income shown in the return.`
  line `( 3 ) No order imposing a penalty under sub-section ( 2 ) shall be made, —`
  line `( a ) unless an assessee has been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard;`
  line `( b ) by the 1 [Assistant Commissioner or Deputy Commissioner] or the 2 [Assistant Director or`
  line `Deputy Director], as the case may be, where the amount of penalty exceeds twenty thousand rupees`
  line `except with the previous approval of the 3 [Joint Commissioner] or the 4 [Joint Director], as the case`
  line `may be;`
  line `( c ) in a case where the assessment is the subject-matter of an appeal to the Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals) under section 246 5 [or section 246A] or an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal under section`
  line `253, after the expiry of the financial year in which the proceedings, in the course of which action for`
  line `the imposition of penalty has been initiated, are completed, or six months from the end of the month`
  line `in which the order of the Commissioner (Appeals) or, as the case may be, the Appellate Tribunal is`
  line `received by the 6 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or the 7 [Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner], whichever period expires later;`
  line `( d ) in a case where the assessment is the subject-matter of revision under section 263, after the`
  line `expiry of six months from the end of the month in which such order of revision is passed;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 3, for “Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for “Assistant Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for “Deputy Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 59 (w.e.f. 1-6-2000).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_613_footnotes:
  string
  line
