obj_root_law_sections_615:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-615
  sectionNo (615)
  orderNo 615
  title `Page 615`
  content obj_root_law_sections_615_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_615_footnotes
  sourcePage 615
obj_root_law_sections_615_content:
  string
  line 615
  line `CHAPTER XV`
  line `L IABILITY IN SPECIAL CASES`
  line `A. — Legal representatives`
  line `159. Legal representatives. — ( 1 ) Where a person dies, his legal representative shall be liable to pay`
  line `any sum which the deceased would have been liable to pay if he had not died, in the like manner and to`
  line `the same extent as the deceased.`
  line `( 2 ) For the purpose of making an assessment (including an assessment, reassessment or`
  line `recomputation under section 147) of the income of the deceased and for the purpose of levying any sum`
  line `in the hands of the legal representative in accordance with the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ), —`
  line `( a ) any proceeding taken against the deceased before his death shall be deemed to have been`
  line `taken against the legal representative and may be continued against the legal representative from the`
  line `stage at which it stood on the date of the death of the deceased;`
  line `( b ) any proceeding which could have been taken against the deceased if he had survived, may be`
  line `taken against the legal representative; and`
  line `( c ) all the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly.`
  line `( 3 ) The legal representative of the deceased shall, for the purposes of this Act, be deemed to be an`
  line assessee.
  line `( 4 ) Every legal representative shall be personally liable for any tax payable by him in his capacity as`
  line `legal representative if, while his liability for tax remains undischarged, he creates a charge on or disposes`
  line `of or parts with any assets of the estate of the deceased, which are in, or may come into, his possession,`
  line `but such liability shall be limited to the value of the asset so charged, disposed of or parted with.`
  line `( 5 ) The provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 161, section 162, and section 167, shall, so far as may`
  line `be and to the extent to which they are not inconsistent with the provisions of this section, apply in relation`
  line `to a legal representative.`
  line `( 6 ) The liability of a legal representative under this section shall, subject to the provisions of sub-`
  line `section ( 4 ) and sub-section ( 5 ), be limited to the extent to which the estate is capable of meeting the`
  line liability.
  line `B. — Representative assessees - General provisions`
  line `160. Representative assessee. — ( 1 ) For the purposes of this Act, “representative assessee” means—`
  line `( i ) in respect of the income of a non-resident specified in 1 *** sub-section (1) of section 9, the`
  line `agent of the non-resident, including a person who is treated as an agent under section 163;`
  line `( ii ) in respect of the income of a minor, lunatic or idiot, the guardian or manager who is entitled`
  line `to receive or is in receipt of such income on behalf of such minor, lunatic or idiot;`
  line `( iii ) in respect of income which the Court of Wards, the Administrator-General, the Official`
  line `Trustee or any receiver or manager (including any person, whatever his designation, who in fact`
  line `manages property on behalf of another) appointed by or under any order of a court, receives or is`
  line `entitled to receive, on behalf or for the benefit of any person, such Court of Wards, Administrator-`
  line `General, Official Trustee, receiver or manager;`
  line `1. The words, brackets and figure “clause ( i ) of” omitted by Act 66 of 1976, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1 -6-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_615_footnotes:
  string
