obj_root_law_sections_616_content:
  string
  line 616
  line `( iv ) in respect of income which a trustee appointed under a trust declared by a duly executed`
  line `instrument in writing whether testamentary or otherwise [including any wakf deed which is valid`
  line `under the Mussalman Wakf Validating Act, 1913 (6 of 1913),] receives or is entitled to receive on`
  line `behalf or for the benefit of any person, such trustee or trustees;`
  line `1 [( v ) in respect of income which a trustee appointed under an oral trust receives or is entitled to`
  line `receive on behalf or for the benefit of any person, such trustee or trustees.`
  line `Explanation 1. — A trust which is not declared by a duly executed instrument in writing [including`
  line `any wakf deed which is valid under the Mussalman Wakf Validating Act, 1913 (6 of 1913),] shall be`
  line `deemed, for the purposes of clause ( iv ), to be a trust declared by a duly executed instrument in writing if a`
  line `statement in writing, signed by the trustee or trustees, setting out the purpose or purposes of the trust,`
  line `particulars as to the trustee or trustees, the beneficiary or beneficiaries and the trust property, is forwarded`
  line `to the 2 [Assessing Officer], —`
  line `( i ) where the trust has been declared before the 1st day of June, 1981, within a period of three`
  line `months from that day; and`
  line `( ii ) in any other case, within three months from the date of declaration of the trust.`
  line `Explanation 2. — For the purposes of clause ( v ), “oral trust” means a trust which is not declared by a`
  line `duly executed instrument in writing [including any wakf deed which is valid under the Mussalman Wakf`
  line `Validating Act, 1913 (6 of 1913),] and which is not deemed under Explanation 1 to be a trust declared by`
  line `a duly executed instrument in writing.]`
  line `( 2 ) Every representative assessee shall be deemed to be an assessee for the purposes of this Act.`
  line `161. Liability of representative assessee. — ( 1 ) Every representative assessee, as regards the income`
  line `in respect of which he is a representative assessee, shall be subject to the same duties, responsibilities and`
  line `liabilities as if the income were income received by or accruing to or in favour of him beneficially, and`
  line `shall be liable to assessment in his own name in respect of that income; but any such assessment shall be`
  line `deemed to be made upon him in his representative capacity only, and the tax shall, subject to the other`
  line `provisions contained in this Chapter, be levied upon and recovered from him in like manner and to the`
  line `same extent as it would be leviable upon and recoverable from the person represented by him.`
  line `3 [( 1A ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), where any income in respect of which`
  line `the person mentioned in clause ( iv ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 160 is liable as representative assessee`
  line `consists of, or includes, profits and gains of business, tax shall be charged on the whole of the income in`
  line `respect of which such person is so liable at the maximum marginal rate:`
  line `Provided that the provisions of this sub-section shall not apply where such profits and gains are`
  line `receivable under a trust declared by any person by will exclusively for the benefit of any relative`
  line `dependent on him for support and maintenance, and such trust is the only trust so declared by him.`
  line `4 * * * * *]`
  line `( 2 ) Where any person is, in respect of any income, assessable under this Chapter in the capacity of a`
  line `representative assessee, he shall not, in respect of that income, be assessed under any other provision of`
  line `this Act.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 16 of 1981, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-1981).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `4. The Explanation omitted by Act 49 of 1991, s. 49 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_616_footnotes:
