  line
obj_root_law_sections_617:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-617
  sectionNo (617)
  orderNo 617
  title `Page 617`
  content obj_root_law_sections_617_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_617_footnotes
  sourcePage 617
obj_root_law_sections_617_content:
  string
  line 617
  line `162. Right of representative assessee to recover tax paid. — ( 1 ) Every representative assessee who,`
  line `as such, pays any sum under this Act, shall be entitled to recover the sum so paid from the person on`
  line `whose behalf it is paid, or to retain out of any moneys that may be in his possession or may come to him`
  line `in his representative capacity, an amount equal to the sum so paid.`
  line `( 2 ) Any representative assessee, or any person who apprehends that he may be assessed as a`
  line `representative assessee, may retain out of any money payable by him to the person on whose behalf he is`
  line `liable to pay tax (hereinafter in this section referred to as the principal), a sum equal to his estimated`
  line `liability under this Chapter, and in the event of any disagreement between the principal and such`
  line `representative assessee or person as to the amount to be so retained, such representative assessee or`
  line `person may secure from the 1 [Assessing Officer] a certificate stating the amount to be so retained pending`
  line `final settlement of the liability, and the certificate so obtained shall be his warrant for retaining that`
  line amount.
  line `( 3 ) The amount recoverable from such representative assessee or person at the time of final settlement`
  line `shall not exceed the amount specified in such certificate, except to the extent to which such representative`
  line `assessee or person may at such time have in his hands additional assets of the principal.`
  line `C. — Representative assessees — Special cases`
  line `163. Who may be regarded as agent. — ( 1 ) For the purposes of this Act, “agent”, in relation to a`
  line `non-resident, includes any person in India —`
  line `( a ) who is employed by or on behalf of the non-resident; or`
  line `( b ) who has any business connection with the non-resident; or`
  line `( c ) from or through whom the non-resident is in receipt of any income, whether directly or`
  line `indirectly; or`
  line `( d ) who is the trustee of the non-resident;`
  line `and includes also any other person who, whether a resident or non-resident, has acquired by means of a`
  line `transfer, a capital asset in India:`
  line `Provided that a broker in India who, in respect of any transactions, does not deal directly with or on`
  line `behalf of a non-resident principal but deals with or through a non-resident broker shall not be deemed to`
  line `be an agent under this section in respect of such transactions, if the following conditions are fulfilled,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( i ) the transactions are carried on in the ordinary course of business through the first-mentioned`
  line `broker; and`
  line `( ii ) the non-resident broker is carrying on such transactions in the ordinary course of his business`
  line `and not as a principal.`
  line `2 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- section, the expression “business connection” shall have`
  line `the meaning assigned to it in Explanation 2 to clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 9 of this Act.]`
  line `( 2 ) No person shall be treated as the agent of a non-resident unless he has had an opportunity of being`
  line `heard by the 1 [Assessing Officer] as to his liability to be treated as such.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 68 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_617_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_618:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-618
  sectionNo (618)
