  title `Page 618`
  content obj_root_law_sections_618_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_618_footnotes
  sourcePage 618
obj_root_law_sections_618_content:
  string
  line 618
  line `1 [ 164. Charge of tax where share of beneficiaries unknown. — 2 [( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of`
  line `sub-sections ( 2 ) and ( 3 ), where] any income in respect of which the persons mentioned in clauses ( iii ) and`
  line `( iv ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 160 are liable as representative assessees or any part thereof is not`
  line `specifically receivable on behalf or for the benefit of any one person or where the individual shares of the`
  line `persons on whose behalf or for whose benefit such income or such part thereof is receivable are`
  line `indeterminate or unknown (such income, such part of the income and such persons being hereafter in this`
  line `section referred to as “relevant income”, “part of relevant income” and “beneficiaries”, respectively),`
  line `3 [tax shall be charged on the relevant income or part of relevant income at the maximum marginal rate]:`
  line `Provided that in a case where —`
  line `4 [( i ) none of the beneficiaries has any other income chargeable under this Act exceeding the`
  line `maximum amount not chargeable to tax in the case of an 5 [association of persons] or is a beneficiary`
  line `under any other trust; or]`
  line `( ii ) the relevant income or part of relevant income is receivable 6 [under a trust declared by any`
  line `person by will and such trust is the only trust so declared by him]; or`
  line `( iii ) the relevant income or part of relevant income is receivable under a trust created before the`
  line `1st day of March, 1970, by a non-testamentary instrument and the 7 [Assessing Officer] is satisfied,`
  line `having regard to all the circumstances existing at the relevant time, that the trust was created bona`
  line `fide exclusively for the benefit of the relatives of the settlor, or where the settlor is a Hindu undivided`
  line `family, exclusively for the benefit of the members of such family, in circumstances where such`
  line `relatives or members were mainly dependent on the settlor for their support and maintenance; or`
  line `( iv ) the relevant income is receivable by the trustees on behalf of a provident fund,`
  line `superannuation fund, gratuity fund, pension fund or any other fund created bona fide by a person`
  line `carrying on a business or profession exclusively for the benefit of persons employed in such business`
  line `or profession,`
  line `tax shall be charged 8 [on the relevant income or part of relevant income as if it] were the total income of`
  line `an 5 [association of persons]:]`
  line `9 [Provided further that where any income in respect of which the person mentioned in clause ( iv ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 160 is liable as representative assessee consists of, or includes, profits and gains`
  line `of business, the preceding proviso shall apply only if such profits and gains are receivable under a trust`
  line `declared by any person by will exclusively for the benefit of any relative dependent on him for support`
  line `and maintenance, and such trust is the only trust so declared by him.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1970, s. 21, for section 164 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `2. Restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4- 1989). Earlier the words “( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of sub-sections ( 2 ) and`
  line `( 3 ), w here” substituted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 64 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 27, for the portion beginning with the words “tax shall be charged—” and ending with the`
  line `words “more beneficial to the revenue” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1980).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 27, ibid., for clause ( i ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1980).`
  line `5. Restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4- 1989). Earlier the words “association of persons” substituted by Act 4 of`
  line `1988, s. 64 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 27, for “under a trust declared by will” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1980).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 27, for “as if the relevant income or part of relevant income” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1980).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
