obj_root_law_sections_619_content:
  string
  line 619
  line `1 [( 2 ) In the case of relevant income which is derived from property held under trust wholly for`
  line `charitable or religious purposes, 2 [or which is of the nature referred to in sub-clause ( iia ) of clause ( 24 )`
  line `of section 2, 3 [or which is of the nature referred to in sub-section ( 4A ) of section 11,] tax shall be charged`
  line `on so much of the relevant income as is not exempt under section 11 or section 12], as if the relevant`
  line `income not so exempt were the income of an association of persons:`
  line `4 [Provided that in a case where the whole or any part of the relevant income is not exempt`
  line `under section 11 or section 12 by virtue of the provisions contained in clause ( c ) or clause ( d ) of sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ) of section 13, tax shall be charged [on the relevant income or part of relevant income at the`
  line `maximum marginal rate.]]`
  line `( 3 ) 5 [In a case where the relevant income is derived from property held under trust in part only for`
  line `charitable or religious purposes or is of the nature referred to in sub-clause ( iia ) of clause ( 24 ) of section`
  line `2] 3 [or is of thenature referred to in sub-section ( 4A ) of section 11,] and either the relevant income`
  line `applicable to purposes other than charitable or religious purposes (or any part thereof) 6 [is not specifically`
  line `receivable on behalf or for the benefit of any one person or the individual shares of the beneficiaries in the`
  line `income so applicable are indeterminate or unknown, the tax chargeable on the relevant income shall be`
  line `the aggregate of —`
  line `( a ) the tax which would be chargeable on that part of the relevant income which is applicable to`
  line `charitable or religious purposes (as reduced by the income, if any, which is exempt under section 11)`
  line `as if such part (or such part as so reduced) were the total income of an association of persons; and`
  line `( b ) the tax on that part of the relevant income which is applicable to purposes other than`
  line `charitable or religious purposes, and which is either not specifically receivable on behalf or for the`
  line `benefit of any one person or in respect of which the shares of the beneficiaries are indeterminate or`
  line `unknown, at the maximum marginal rate:]`
  line `Provided that in a case where —`
  line `7 [( i ) none of the beneficiaries in respect of the part of the relevant income which is not`
  line `applicable to charitable or religious purposes has any other income chargeable under this Act`
  line `exceeding the maximum amount not chargeable to tax in the case of an association of persons or`
  line `is a beneficiary under any other trust; or]`
  line `( ii ) the relevant income is receivable 8 [under a trust declared by any person by will and such`
  line `trust is the only trust so declared by him]; or`
  line `( iii ) the relevant income is receivable under a trust created before the 1st day of March, 1970,`
  line `by a non-testamentary instrument and the 9 [Assessing Officer] is satisfied, having regard to all the`
  line `circumstances existing at the relevant time, that the trust, to the extent it is not for charitable or`
  line `religious purposes, was created bona fide exclusively for the benefit of the relatives of the settlor,`
  line `or where the settlor is a Hindu undivided family, exclusively for the benefit of the members of`
  line `such family, in circumstances where such relatives or members were mainly dependent on the`
  line `settlor for their support and maintenance,`
  line `1. Restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier sub-section ( 2 ) and ( 3 ) were omitted by Act 4 of 1988,`
  line `s. 64 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 27, for “tax shall be charged on so much of the relevant income as is not exempt under section`
  line `11” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1973).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 11 of 1983, s. 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-1984).`
  line `4. The proviso added by Act 21 of 1984, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 27, for “In a case where the rele vant income is derived from property held under trust in part`
  line `only in charitable or religious purposes” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1973).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 27, for the portion beginning with the words “is not specifically receivable” and ending with`
  line `the wor ds “whichever course would be more beneficial to the revenue:” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1980).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 27, ibid., for clause ( i ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1980).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 27, ibid., for “under a trust declared by will” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1980).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
