obj_root_law_sections_620_content:
  string
  line 620
  line `tax shall be charged 1 [on the relevant income as if the relevant income] (as reduced by the income, if any,`
  line `which is exempt under section 11) were the total income of an association of persons:]`
  line `2 [Provided further that where the relevant income consists of, or includes, profits and gains of`
  line `business, the preceding proviso shall apply only if the income is receivable under a trust declared by any`
  line `person by will exclusively for the benefit of any relative dependent on him for support and maintenance,`
  line `and such trust is the only trust so declared by him:`
  line `Provided also that in a case where the whole or any part of the relevant income is not exempt`
  line `under section 11 or section 12 by virtue of the provisions contained in clause ( c ) or clause ( d ) of sub-`
  line `section (1) of section 13, tax shall be charged on the relevant income or part of relevant income at the`
  line `maximum marginal rate.]]`
  line `3 [ Explanation 1. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) any income in respect of which the persons mentioned in clause ( iii ) and clause ( iv ) of sub-`
  line `section (1) of section 160 are liable as representative assessee or any part thereof shall be deemed as`
  line `being not specifically receivable on behalf or for the benefit of any one person unless the person on`
  line `whose behalf or for whose benefit such income or such part thereof is receivable during the previous`
  line `year is expressly stated in the order of the court or the instrument of trust or wakf deed, as the case`
  line `may be, and is identifiable as such on the date of such order, instrument or deed;`
  line `( ii ) the individual shares of the persons on whose behalf or for whose benefit such income or`
  line `such part thereof is received shall be deemed to be indeterminate or unknown unless the individual`
  line `shares of the persons on whose behalf or for whose benefit such income or such part thereof is`
  line `receivable, are expressly stated in the order of the court or the instrument of trust or wakf deed, as the`
  line `case may be, and are ascertainable as such on the date of such order, instrument or deed.`
  line `4 * * * * * ]`
  line `5 [ 164A. Charge of tax in case of oral trust. — Where a trustee receives or is entitled to receive any`
  line `income on behalf or for the benefit of any person under an oral trust, then, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other provision of this Act, tax shall be charged on such income at the maximum`
  line `marginal rate.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `6 * * * *`
  line *
  line `( ii ) “oral trust” shall have the meaning assigned to it in Explanation 2 below sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 160.]`
  line `165. Case where part of trust income is chargeable. — Where part only of the income of a trust is`
  line `chargeable under this Act, that proportion only of the income receivable by a beneficiary from the trust`
  line `which the part so chargeable bears to the whole income of the trust shall be deemed to have been derived`
  line `from that part.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 27, for “as if the relevant income” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1980).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-1980).`
  line `4. Explanation 2 omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 64 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 16 of 1981, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-1981).`
  line `6. Clause ( i ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_620_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_621:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-621
  sectionNo (621)
  orderNo 621
  title `Page 621`
  content obj_root_law_sections_621_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_621_footnotes
  sourcePage 621
obj_root_law_sections_621_content:
  string
  line 621
  line `D. — Representative assessees — Miscellaneous provisions`
  line `166.Direct assessment or recovery not barred. — Nothing in the foregoing sections in this Chapter`
  line `shall prevent either the direct assessment of the person on whose behalf or for whose benefit income`
  line `therein referred to is receivable, or the recovery from such person of the tax payable in respect of such`
  line income.
  line `167. Remedies against property in cases of representative assessees. — The 1 [Assessing Officer]`
  line `shall have the same remedies against all property of any kind vested in or under the control or`
  line `management of any representative assessee as he would have against the property of any person liable to`
  line `pay any tax, and in as full and ample a manner, whether the demand is raised against the representative`
  line `assessee or against the beneficiary direct.`
  line `2 [ DD. — Firms, association of persons and body of individuals`
  line `167A.Charge of tax in the case of a firm. — In the case of a firm which is assessable as a firm, tax`
  line `shall be charged on its total income at the 3 [rate as specified in the Finance Act of the relevant year].]`
  line `4 [ 167B.Charge of tax where shares of members in association of persons or body of individuals`
  line `unknown, etc. — ( 1 ) Where the individual shares of the members of an association of persons or body of`
  line `individuals (other than a company or a co-operative society or a society registered under the Societies`
  line `Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860) or under any law corresponding to that Act in force in any part of`
  line `India) in the whole or any part of the income of such association or body are indeterminate or unknown,`
  line `tax shall be charged on the total income of the association or body at the maximum marginal rate:`
  line `Provided that, where the total income of any member of such association or body is chargeable to tax`
  line `at a rate which is higher than the maximum marginal rate, tax shall be charged on the total income of the`
  line `association or body at such higher rate.`
  line `( 2 ) Where, in the case of an association of persons or body of individuals as aforesaid [not being a`
  line `case falling under sub-section ( 1 )], —`
  line `( i ) the total income of any member thereof for the previous year (excluding his share from such`
  line `association or body) exceeds the maximum amount which is not chargeable to tax in the case of that`
  line `member under the Finance Act of the relevant year, tax shall be charged on the total income of the`
  line `association or body at the maximum marginal rate;`
  line `( ii ) any member or members thereof is or are chargeable to tax at a rate or rates which is or are`
  line `higher than the maximum marginal rate, tax shall be charged on that portion or portions of the total`
  line `income of the association or body which is or are relatable to the share or shares of such member or`
  line `members at such higher rate or rates, as the case may be, and the balance of the total income of the`
  line `association or body shall be taxed at the maximum marginal rate.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, the individual shares of the members of an association`
  line `of persons or body of individuals in the whole or any part of the income of such association or body shall`
  line `be deemed to be indeterminate or unknown if such shares (in relation to the whole or any part of such`
  line `income) are indeterminate or unknown on the date of formation of such association or body or at any time`
  line thereafter.]
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 64, for the sub- heading “ DD. — Association of persons and body of individuals ” (w.e.f. 1 -4-`
  line `1993).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 44, for “maximum marginal rate” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1998).`
  line `4.Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_621_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_622:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-622
  sectionNo (622)
  orderNo 622
  title `Page 622`
  content obj_root_law_sections_622_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_622_footnotes
  sourcePage 622
obj_root_law_sections_622_content:
  string
  line 622
  line `1 [ 167C. Liability of partners of limited liability partnership in liquidation. — Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in the Limited Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009), where any tax due from a`
  line `limited liability partnership in respect of any income of any previous year or from any other person in`
  line `respect of any income of any previous year during which such other person was a limited liability`
  line `partnership cannot be recovered, in such case, every person who was a partner of the limited liability`
  line `partnership at any time during the relevant previous year, shall be jointly and severally liable for the`
  line `payment of such tax unless he proves that the non-recovery cannot be attributed to any gross neglect,`
  line `misfeasance or breach of duty on his part in relation to the affairs of the limited liability partnership.]`
  line `2 [ Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, the expression “tax due” includes penalty, interest`
  line `or any other sum payable under the Act.]`
  line `E. — Executors`
  line `168.Executors. — ( 1 ) Subject as hereinafter provided, the income of the estate of a deceased person`
  line `shall be chargeable to tax in the hands of the executor, —`
  line `( a ) if there is only one executor, then, as if the executor were an individual; or`
  line `( b ) if there are more executors than one, then, as if the executors were an association of persons;`
  line `and for the purposes of this Act, the executor shall be deemed to be resident or non-resident according as`
  line `the deceased person was a resident or non-resident during the previous year in which his death took place.`
  line `( 2 ) The assessment of an executor under this section shall be made separately from any assessment`
  line `that may be made on him in respect of his own income.`
  line `( 3 ) Separate assessments shall be made under this section on the total income of each completed`
  line `previous year or part thereof as is included in the period from the date of the death to the date of complete`
  line `distribution to the beneficiaries of the estate according to their several interests.`
  line `( 4 ) In computing the total income of any previous year under this section, any income of the estate of`
  line `that previous year distributed to, or applied to the benefit of, any specific legatee of the estate during that`
  line `previous year shall be excluded; but the income so excluded shall be included in the total income of the`
  line `previous year of such specific legatee.`
  line `Explanation. —In this section, “executor” includes an administrator or other person administer ing the`
  line `estate of a deceased person.`
  line `169. Right of executor to recover tax paid. — The provisions of section 162 shall, so far as may be,`
  line `apply in the case of an executor in respect of tax paid or payable by him as they apply in the case of a`
  line `representative assessee.`
  line `F. — Succession to business or profession`
  line `170. Succession to business otherwise than on death. — ( 1 ) Where a person carrying on any`
  line `business or profession (such person hereinafter in this section being referred to as the predecessor) has`
  line `been succeeded therein by any other person (hereinafter in this section referred to as the successor) who`
  line `continues to carry on that business or profession, —`
  line `( a ) the predecessor shall be assessed in respect of the income of the previous year in which the`
  line `succession took place up to the date of succession;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 59 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 44 (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_622_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_623:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-623
  sectionNo (623)
  orderNo 623
  title `Page 623`
  content obj_root_law_sections_623_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_623_footnotes
  sourcePage 623
obj_root_law_sections_623_content:
  string
  line 623
  line `( b ) the successor shall be assessed in respect of the income of the previous year after the date of`
  line succession.
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), when the predecessor cannot be found, the`
  line `assessment of the income of the previous year in which the succession took place up to the date of`
  line `succession and of the previous year preceding that year shall be made on the successor in like manner and`
  line `to the same extent as it would have been made on the predecessor, and all the provisions of this Act shall,`
  line `so far as may be, apply accordingly.`
  line `( 3 ) When any sum payable under this section in respect of the income of such business or profession`
  line `for the previous year in which the succession took place up to the date of succession or for the previous`
  line `year preceding that year, assessed on the predecessor, cannot be recovered from him, the 1 [Assessing`
  line `Officer] shall record a finding to that effect and the sum payable by the predecessor shall thereafter be`
  line `payable by and recoverable from the successor, and the successor shall be entitled to recover from the`
  line `predecessor any sum so paid.`
  line `( 4 ) Where any business or profession carried on by a Hindu undivided family is succeeded to, and`
  line `simultaneously with the succession or after the succession there has been a partition of the joint family`
  line `property between the members or groups of members, the tax due in respect of the income of the business`
  line `or profession succeeded to, up to the date of succession, shall be assessed and recovered in the manner`
  line `provided in section 171, but without prejudice to the provisions of this section.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, “income” includes any gain accruing from the`
  line `transfer, in any manner whatsoever, of the business or profession as a result of the succession.`
  line `G. — Partition`
  line `171. Assessment after partition of a Hindu undivided family. — ( 1 ) A Hindu family hitherto`
  line `assessed as undivided shall be deemed for the purposes of this Act to continue to be a Hindu undivided`
  line `family, except where and in so far as a finding of partition has been given under this section in respect of`
  line `the Hindu undivided family.`
  line `( 2 ) Where, at the time of making an assessment under section 143 or section 144, it is claimed by or`
  line `on behalf of any member of a Hindu family assessed as undivided that a partition, whether total or partial,`
  line `has taken place among the members of such family, the 1 [Assessing Officer] shall make an inquiry`
  line `thereinto after giving notice of the inquiry to all the members of the family.`
  line `( 3 ) On the completion of the inquiry, the 1 [Assessing Officer] shall record a finding as to whether`
  line `there has been a total or partial partition of the joint family property, and, if there has been such a`
  line `partition, the date on which it has taken place.`
  line `( 4 ) Where a finding of total or partial partition has been recorded by the 1 [Assessing Officer] under`
  line `this section, and the partition took place during the previous year, —`
  line `( a ) the total income of the joint family in respect of the period up to the date of partition shall be`
  line `assessed as if no partition had taken place; and`
  line `( b ) each member or group of members shall, in addition to any tax for which he or it may be`
  line `separately liable and notwithstanding anything contained in clause ( 2 ) of section 10, be jointly and`
  line `severally liable for the tax on the income so assessed.`
  line `( 5 ) Where a finding of total or partial partition has been recorded by the 1 [Assessing Officer] under`
  line `this section, and the partition took place after the expiry of the previous year, the total income of the`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
