  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_624_footnotes
  sourcePage 624
obj_root_law_sections_624_content:
  string
  line 624
  line `previous year of the joint family shall be assessed as if no partition had taken place; and the provisions of`
  line `clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 4 ) shall, so far as may be, apply to the case.`
  line `( 6 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, if the 1 [Assessing Officer] finds after`
  line `completion of the assessment of a Hindu undivided family that the family has already effected a partition,`
  line `whether total or partial, the 1 [Assessing Officer] shall proceed to recover the tax from every person who`
  line `was a member of the family before the partition, and every such person shall be jointly and severally`
  line `liable for the tax on the income so assessed.`
  line `( 7 ) For the purposes of this section, the several liability of any member or group of members`
  line `thereunder shall be computed according to the portion of the joint family property allotted to him or it at`
  line `the partition, whether total or partial.`
  line `( 8 ) The provisions of this section shall, so far as may be, apply in relation to the levy and collection of`
  line `any penalty, interest, fine or other sum in respect of any period up to date of the partition, whether total or`
  line `partial, of a Hindu undivided family as they apply in relation to the levy and collection of tax in respect of`
  line `any such period.`
  line `2 [( 9 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, where a partial`
  line `partition has taken place after the 31st day of December, 1978, among the members of a Hindu undivided`
  line `family hitherto assessed as undivided, —`
  line `( a ) no claim that such partial partition has taken place shall be inquired into under sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `and no finding shall be recorded under sub-section ( 3 ) that such partial partition had taken place and`
  line `any finding recorded under sub-section ( 3 ) to that effect whether before or after the 18th day of June,`
  line `1980, being the date of introduction of the Finance (No. 2) Bill, 1980, shall be null and void;`
  line `( b ) such family shall continue to be liable to be assessed under this Act as if no such partial`
  line `partition had taken place;`
  line `( c ) each member or group of members of such family immediately before such partial partition`
  line `and the family shall be jointly and severally liable for any tax, penalty, interest, fine or other sum`
  line `payable under this Act by the family in respect of any period, whether before or after such partial`
  line partition;
  line `( d ) the several liability of any member or group of members aforesaid shall be computed`
  line `according to the portion of the joint family property allotted to him or it at such partial partition,`
  line `and the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly.]`
  line `Explanation. — In this section, —`
  line `( a ) “partition” means—`
  line `( i ) where the property admits of a physical division, a physical division of the property, but a`
  line `physical division of the income without a physical division of the property producing the income`
  line `shall not be deemed to be a partition; or`
  line `( ii ) where the property does not admit of a physical division, then such division as the`
  line `property admits of, but a mere severance of status shall not be deemed to be a partition;`
  line `( b ) “partial partition” means a partition which is partial as regards the persons constituting the`
  line `Hindu undivided family, or the properties belonging to the Hindu undivided family, or both.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1-4-1980).`
obj_root_law_sections_624_footnotes:
