obj_root_law_sections_625_content:
  string
  line 625
  line `H. — Profits of non-residents from occasional shipping business`
  line `172. Shipping business of non-residents. — ( 1 ) The provisions of this section shall, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in the other provisions of this Act, apply for the purpose of the levy and recovery of`
  line `tax in the case of any ship, belonging to or chartered by a non-resident, which carries passengers,`
  line `livestock, mail or goods shipped at a port in India 1 ***.`
  line `( 2 ) Where such a ship carries passengers, livestock, mail or goods shipped at a port in India, 2 [seven`
  line `and a half per cent.] of the amount paid or payable on account of such carriage to the owner or the`
  line `charterer or to any person on his behalf, whether that amount is paid or payable in or out of India, shall be`
  line `deemed to be income accruing in India to the owner or charterer on account of such carriage.`
  line `( 3 ) Before the departure from any port in India of any such ship, the master of the ship shall prepare`
  line `and furnish to the 3 [Assessing Officer] a return of the full amount paid or payable to the owner or`
  line `charterer or any person on his behalf, on account of the carriage of all passengers, livestock, mail or`
  line `goods shipped at that port since the last arrival of the ship thereat:`
  line `Provided that where the 3 [Assessing Officer] is satisfied that it is not possible for the master of the`
  line `ship to furnish the return required by this sub-section before the departure of the ship from the port and`
  line `provided the master of the ship has made satisfactory arrangements for the filing of the return and`
  line `payment of the tax by any other person on his behalf, the 3 [Assessing Officer] may, if the return is filed`
  line `within thirty days of the departure of the ship, deem the filing of the return by the person so authorised by`
  line `the master as sufficient compliance with this sub-section.`
  line `( 4 ) On receipt of the return, the 3 [Assessing Officer] shall assess the income referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) and determine the sum payable as tax thereon at the 4 [rate or rates in force] applicable to`
  line `the total income of a company which has not made the arrangements referred to in section 194 and such`
  line `sum shall be payable by the master of the ship.`
  line `5 [( 4A ) No order assessing the income and determining the sum of tax payable thereon shall be made`
  line `under sub-section ( 4 ) after the expiry of nine months from the end of the financial year in which the`
  line `return under sub-section ( 3 ) is furnished:`
  line `Provided that where the return under sub-section ( 3 ) has been furnished before the 1st day of April,`
  line `2007, such order shall be made on or before the 31st day of December, 2008.]`
  line `( 5 ) For the purpose of determining the tax payable under sub-section ( 4 ), the 3 [Assessing Officer]`
  line `may call for such accounts or documents as he may require.`
  line `( 6 ) A port clearance shall not be granted to the ship until the Collector of Customs, or other officer`
  line `duly authorised to grant the same, is satisfied that the tax assessable under this section has been duly paid`
  line `or that satisfactory arrangements have been made for the payment thereof.`
  line `( 7 ) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to prevent the owner or charterer of a ship from claiming`
  line `before the expiry of the assessment year relevant to the previous year in which the date of departure of the`
  line `ship from the Indian port falls, that an assessment be made of his total income of the previous year and`
  line `the tax payable on the basis thereof be determined in accordance with the other provisions of this Act, and`
  line `if he so claims, any payment made under this section in respect of the passengers, livestock, mail or goods`
  line `shipped at Indian ports during that previous year shall be treated as a payment in advance of the tax`
  line `1. The certain words omitted by Act 25 of 1975, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-6-1975).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for “one - sixth” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1975).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 29, for “rate or rates for the time being” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1967).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 51 (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
