obj_root_law_sections_626_content:
  string
  line 626
  line `leviable for that assessment year, and the difference between the sum so paid and the amount of tax found`
  line `payable by him on such assessment shall be paid by him or refunded to him, as the case may be.`
  line `1 [( 8 ) For the purposes of this section, the amount referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) shall include the`
  line `amount paid or payable by way of demurrage charge or handling charge or any other amount of similar`
  line nature.]
  line `I. — Recovery of tax in respect of non-residents`
  line `173. Recovery of tax in respect of non-resident from his assets. — Without prejudice to the`
  line `provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 161 or of section 167, where the person entitled to the income`
  line `referred to in clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 9 is a non-resident, the tax chargeable thereon,`
  line `whether in his name or in the name of his agent who is liable as a representative assessee, may be`
  line `recovered by deduction under any of the provisions of Chapter XVII-B and any arrears of tax may be`
  line `recovered also in accordance with the provisions of this Act from any assets of the non-resident which`
  line `are, or may at any time come, within India.`
  line `J. — Persons leaving India`
  line `174. Assessment of persons leaving India. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 4,`
  line `when it appears to the 2 [Assessing Officer] that any individual may leave India during the current`
  line `assessment year or shortly after its expiry and that he has no present intention of returning to India, the`
  line `total income of such individual for the period from the expiry of the previous year for that assessment`
  line `year up to the probable date of his departure from India shall be chargeable to tax in that assessment year.`
  line `( 2 ) The total income of each completed previous year or part of any previous year included in such`
  line `period shall be chargeable to tax at the rate or rates in force in that assessment year, and separate`
  line `assessments shall be made in respect of each such completed previous year or part of any previous year.`
  line `( 3 ) The 2 [Assessing Officer] may estimate the income of such individual for such period or any part`
  line `thereof, where it cannot be readily determined in the manner provided in this Act.`
  line `( 4 ) For the purpose of making an assessment under sub-section ( 1 ), the 2 [Assessing Officer] may`
  line `serve a notice upon such individual requiring him to furnish within such time, not being less than seven`
  line `days, as may be specified in the notice, a return in the same form and verified in the same manner 3 [as a`
  line `return under clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142], setting forth his total income for each completed`
  line `previous year comprised in the period referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) and his estimated total income for any`
  line `part of the previous year comprised in that period; and the provisions of this Act shall, so far as may be,`
  line `and subject to the provisions of this section, apply as if the notice were 4 [a notice issued under clause ( i )`
  line `of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142].`
  line `( 5 ) The tax chargeable under this section shall be in addition to the tax, if any, chargeable under any`
  line `other provision of this Act.`
  line `( 6 ) Where the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) are applicable, any notice issued by the 2 [Assessing`
  line `Officer] under 5 [clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142 or] section 148 in respect of any tax`
  line `chargeable under any other provision of this Act may, notwithstanding anything contained in 5 [clause ( i )`
  line `of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142 or] section 148, as the case may be, require the furnishing of the return`
  line `by such individual within such period, not being less than seven days, as the 2 [Assessing Officer] may`
  line `think proper.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w. e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 126, ibid., for “as a return under sub -section ( 2 ) of section 139” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 126, ibid., for “a notice issued under sub -section ( 2 ) of section 139” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 126, ibid., for “su b-section ( 2 ) of section 139 or sub-section ( 1 ) of” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
