obj_root_law_sections_627_content:
  string
  line 627
  line `1 [ JA. — Association of persons or body of individuals or`
  line `artificial juridical person formed for a particular event or purpose`
  line `174A. Assessment of association of persons or body of individuals or artificial juridical person`
  line `formed for a particular event or purpose. — Notwithstanding anything contained in section 4, where it`
  line `appears to the Assessing Officer that any association of persons or a body of individuals or an artificial`
  line `juridical person, formed or established or incorporated for a particular event or purpose is likely to be`
  line `dissolved in the assessment year in which such association of persons or a body of individuals or an`
  line `artificial juridical person was formed or established or incorporated or immediately after such assessment`
  line `year, the total income of such association or body or juridical person for the period from the expiry of the`
  line `previous year for that assessment year up to the date of its dissolution shall be chargeable to tax in that`
  line `assessment year, and the provisions of sub-sections ( 2 ) to ( 6 ) of section 174 shall, so far as may be, apply`
  line `to any proceedings in the case of any such person as they apply in the case of persons leaving India.]`
  line `K. — Persons trying to alienate their assets`
  line `175. Assessment of persons likely to transfer property to avoid tax. — Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 4, if it appears to the 2 [Assessing Officer] during any current assessment year that`
  line `any person is likely to charge, sell, transfer, dispose of or otherwise part with any of his assets with a view`
  line `to avoiding payment of any liability under the provisions of this Act, the total income of such person for`
  line `the period from the expiry of the previous year for that assessment year to the date when the`
  line `2 [AssessingOfficer] commences proceedings under this section shall be chargeable to tax in that`
  line `assessment year, and the provisions of sub-sections ( 2 ), ( 3 ), ( 4 ), ( 5 ) and ( 6 ) of section 174 shall, so far as`
  line `may be, apply to any proceedings in the case of any such person as they apply in the case of persons`
  line `leaving India`
  line `L. — Discontinuance of business, or dissolution`
  line `176. Discontinued business. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 4, where any`
  line `business or profession is discontinued in any assessment year, the income of the period from the expiry of`
  line `the previous year for that assessment year up to the date of such discontinuance may, at the discretion of`
  line `the 2 [Assessing Officer], be charged to tax in that assessment year.`
  line `( 2 ) The total income of each completed previous year or part of any previous year included in such`
  line `period shall be chargeable to tax at the rate or rates in force in that assessment year, and separate`
  line `assessments shall be made in respect of each such completed previous year or part of any previous year.`
  line `( 3 ) Any person discontinuing any business or profession shall give to the 2 [Assessing Officer] notice`
  line `of such discontinuance within fifteen days thereof.`
  line `3 [( 3A ) Where any business is discontinued in any year, any sum received after the discontinuance`
  line `shall be deemed to be the income of the recipient and charged to tax accordingly in the year of receipt, if`
  line `such sum would have been included in the total income of the person who carried on the business had`
  line `such sum been received before such discontinuance.]`
  line `( 4 ) Where any profession is discontinued in any year on account of the cessation of the profession by,`
  line `or the retirement or death of, the person carrying on the profession, any sum received after the`
  line `discontinuance shall be deemed to be the income of the recipient and charged to tax accordingly in the`
  line `year of receipt, if such sum would have been included in the total income of the aforesaid person had it`
  line `been received before such discontinuance.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 69 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 49 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_627_footnotes:
