  content obj_root_law_sections_628_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_628_footnotes
  sourcePage 628
obj_root_law_sections_628_content:
  string
  line 628
  line `( 5 ) Where an assessment is to be made under the provisions of this section, the 1 [Assessing Officer]`
  line `may serve on the person whose income is to be assessed or, in the case of a firm, on any person who was`
  line `a partner of such firm at the time of its discontinuance or, in the case of a company, on the principal`
  line `officer thereof, a notice containing all or any of the requirements which may be included in a notice`
  line `2 [under clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) ofsection 142] and the provisions of this Act shall, so far as may be,`
  line `apply accordingly as if the notice were a notice issued 2 [under clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 142].`
  line `( 6 ) The tax chargeable under this section shall be in addition to the tax, if any, chargeable under any`
  line `other provision of this Act.`
  line `( 7 ) Where the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) are applicable, any notice issued by the 1 [Assessing`
  line `Officer] under 3 [clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142 or] section 148 in respect of any tax`
  line `chargeable under any other provisions of this Act may, notwithstanding anything contained in 3 [clause ( i )`
  line `of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142 or] section 148, as the case may be, require the furnishing of the return`
  line `by the person to whom the aforesaid notices are issued within such period, not being less than seven days,`
  line `as the 1 [Assessing Officer] may think proper.`
  line `177. Association dissolved or business discontinued. — ( 1 ) Where any business or profession carried`
  line `on by an association of persons has been discontinued or where an association of persons is dissolved, the`
  line `1 [Assessing Officer] shall make an assessment of the total income of the association of persons as if no`
  line `such discontinuance or dissolution had taken place, and all the provisions of this Act, including the`
  line `provisions relating to the levy of a penalty or any other sum chargeable under any provision of this Act`
  line `shall apply, so far as may be, to such assessment.`
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing sub-section, if the 1 [Assessing Officer] or the`
  line `4 [*** Commissioner (Appeals)] in the course of any proceeding under this Act in respect of any such`
  line `association of persons as is referred to in that sub-section is satisfied that the association of persons was`
  line `guilty of any of the acts specified in Chapter XXI, he may impose or direct the imposition of a penalty in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of that Chapter.`
  line `( 3 ) Every person who was at the time of such discontinuance or dissolution a member of the`
  line `association of persons, and the legal representative of any such person who is deceased, shall be jointly`
  line `and severally liable for the amount of tax, penalty or other sum payable, and all the provisions of this Act,`
  line `so far as may be, shall apply to any such assessment or imposition of penalty or other sum.`
  line `( 4 ) Where such discontinuance or dissolution takes place after any proceedings in respect of an`
  line `assessment year have commenced, the proceedings may be continued against the persons referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ) from the stage at which the proceedings stood at the time of such discontinuance or`
  line `dissolution, and all the provisions of this Act shall, so far as may be, apply accordingly.`
  line `( 5 ) Nothing in this section shall affect the provisions of sub-section ( 6 ) of section 159.`
  line `1. S ubs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 126, for “under sub -section ( 2 ) of section 139” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 126, ibid., for “sub -section ( 2 ) of section 139 or sub-section ( 1 ) of” (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. The words and brackets “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or the” omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `Which was earlier substituted as “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)” for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” by Act 4`
  line `of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4- 1988) and The words and brackets “or the commissioner (Appeals)” were inserted by Act 22 of`
  line `1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-1977).`
obj_root_law_sections_628_footnotes:
  string
