obj_root_law_sections_629_content:
  string
  line 629
  line `178. Company in liquidation. — ( 1 ) Every person —`
  line `( a ) who is the liquidator of any company which is being wound up, whether under the orders of a`
  line `court or otherwise; or`
  line `( b ) who has been appointed the receiver of any assets of a company,`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as the liquidator) shall, within thirty days after he has become such liquidator, give`
  line `notice of his appointment as such to the 1 [Assessing Officer] who is entitled to assess the income of the`
  line company.
  line `( 2 ) The 1 [Assessing Officer] shall, after making such inquiries or calling for such information as he`
  line `may deem fit, notify to the liquidator within three months from the date on which he receives notice of`
  line `the appointment of the liquidator the amount which, in the opinion of the 1 [Assessing Officer], would be`
  line `sufficient to provide for any tax which is then, or is likely thereafter to become, payable by the company.`
  line `2 [( 3 ) The liquidator —`
  line `( a ) shall not, without the leave of the 3 [ 4 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner]`
  line `or 5 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]], part with any of the assets of the company or the`
  line `properties in his hands until he has been notified by the 1 [Assessing Officer] under sub-section ( 2 );`
  line and
  line `( b ) on being so notified, shall set aside an amount, equal to the amount notified and, until he so`
  line `sets aside such amount, shall not part with any of the assets of the company or the properties in his`
  line `hands:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall debar the liquidator from parting with such`
  line `assets or properties for the purpose of the payment of the tax payable by the company or for making any`
  line `payment to secured creditors whose debts are entitled under law to priority of payment over debts due to`
  line `Government on the date of liquidation or for meeting such costs and expenses of the winding up of the`
  line `company as are in the opinion of the 3 [ 4 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or`
  line `5 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] reasonable.`
  line `( 4 ) If the liquidator fails to give the notice in accordance with sub-section ( 1 ) or fails to set aside the`
  line `amount as required by sub-section ( 3 ) or parts with any of the assets of the company or the properties in`
  line `his hands in contravention of the provisions of that sub-section, he shall be personally liable for the`
  line `payment of the tax which the company would be liable to pay:`
  line `Provided that if the amount of any tax payable by the company is notified under sub-section ( 2 ), the`
  line `personal liability of the liquidator under this sub-section shall be to the extent of such amount.]`
  line `( 5 ) Where there are more liquidators than one, the obligations and liabilities attached to the liquidator`
  line `under this section shall attach to all the liquidators jointly and severally.`
  line `( 6 ) The provisions of this section shall have effect notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained`
  line `in any other law for the time being in force 6 [except the provisions of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy`
  line `Code, 2016].`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 41, for sub-sections ( 3 ) and ( 4 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 247 and the Third Schedule (w.e.f. 1-11-2016).`
