obj_root_law_sections_630_content:
  string
  line 630
  line `1 [ M. — Private companies ]`
  line `179. Liability of directors of private company in liquidation. — 2 [( 1 )] 3 [Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), where any tax due from a private company in respect`
  line `of any income of any previous year or from any other company in respect of any income of any previous`
  line `year during which such other company was a private company] cannot be recovered, then, every person`
  line `who was a director of the private company at any time during the relevant previous year shall be jointly`
  line `and severally liable for the payment of such tax unless he proves that the non-recovery cannot be`
  line `attributed to any gross neglect, misfeasance or breach of duty on his part in relation to the affairs of the`
  line company.
  line `4 [( 2 ) Where a private company is converted into a public company and the tax assessed in respect of`
  line `any income of any previous year during which such company was a private company cannot be`
  line `recovered, then, nothing contained in sub-section ( 1 ) shall apply to any person who was a director of such`
  line `private company in relation to any tax due in respect of any income of such private company assessable`
  line `for any assessment year commencing before the 1st day of April, 1962.]`
  line `5 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, the express ion “tax due” includes penalty, interest`
  line `or any other sum payable under the Act.]`
  line `N. — Special provisions for certain kinds of income`
  line `180. Royalties or copyright fees for literary or artistic work. — Where the time taken by the author`
  line `of a literary or artistic work in the making thereof is more than twelve months, the amount received or`
  line `receivable by him during any previous year on account of any lump sum consideration for the assignment`
  line `or grant of any of his interests in the copyright of that work or of royalties or copyright fees (whether`
  line `receivable in lump sum or otherwise), in respect of that work, shall, if he so claims, be allocated for`
  line `purposes of assessment in such manner and to such period as may be prescribed:`
  line `6 [Provided that nothing contained in this section shall apply in relation to the previous year relevant to`
  line `the assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 2000.]`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, the expression “author” includes a joint author, and`
  line `the expression “lump sum”, in regard to royalties or copyright fees, includes an advance payment on`
  line `account of such royalties or copyright fees which is not returnable.`
  line `7 [ 180A. Consideration for know-how. — Where the time taken by an individual, who is resident in`
  line `India, for developing any know-how is more than twelve months, he may elect that the gross amount of`
  line `any lump sum consideration received or receivable by him 8 [during the previous year relevant to the`
  line `assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 2000 or earlier assessment years] for allowing use`
  line `of such know-how shall be treated for the purposes of charging income-tax for that year and for each of`
  line `the two immediately preceding previous years as if one-third thereof were included in his income`
  line `chargeable to tax for each of those years respectively and if he so elects, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other provision of this Act, —`
  line `( a ) such gross amount shall be so treated, and`
  line `( b ) the assessments for each of the two preceding previous years shall, if made, be accordingly`
  line `rectified under section 154, the period of four years specified in sub-section ( 7 ) of that section being`
  line `reckoned from the end of the financial year in which the assessment relating to the previous year in`
  line `which the amount was received or receivable by such individual is made.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 50, for “ M. — Private company in liquidation ” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1975).`
  line `2. Section 179 re-numbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by s. 50, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 50, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 50, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 67 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 32 of 1985, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-4-1986).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 68, for “during the previous year” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2000).`
