obj_root_law_sections_631_content:
  string
  line 631
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, the expression “know - how” has the meaning assigned`
  line `to it in section 35AB.]`
  line `1 ***`
  line `CHAPTER XVI`
  line `S PECIAL PROVISIONS APPLICABLE TO FIRMS`
  line `2 [ A. — Assessment of firms`
  line `182. [ Assessment of registered firms.] — Omitted by the Finance Act, 1992, (18 of 1992), s. 65`
  line `( w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `183. [ Assessment of unregistered firms. ] — Omitted by the Finance Act, 1992, (18 of 1992), s. 65`
  line `( w.e.f. 1-4-1993).]`
  line `3 [ 184. Assessment as a firm. — ( 1 ) A firm shall be assessed as a firm for the purposes of this Act, if —`
  line `( i ) the partnership is evidenced by an instrument; and`
  line `( ii ) the individual shares of the partners are specified in that instrument.`
  line `( 2 ) A certified copy of the instrument of partnership referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall accompany`
  line `the return of income of the firm of the previous year relevant to the assessment year commencing on or`
  line `after the 1st day of April, 1993 in respect of which assessment as a firm is first sought.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, the copy of the instrument of partnership shall be`
  line `certified in writing by all the partners (not being minors) or, where the return is made after the dissolution`
  line `of the firm, by all persons (not being minors) who were partners in the firm immediately before its`
  line `dissolution and by the legal representative of any such partner who is deceased.`
  line `( 3 ) Where a firm is assessed as such for any asses9+sment year, it shall be assessed in the same`
  line `capacity for every subsequent year if there is no change in the constitution of the firm or the shares of the`
  line `partners as evidenced by the instrument of partnership on the basis of which the assessment as a firm was`
  line `first sought.`
  line `(4) Where any such change had taken place in the previous year, the firm shall furnish a certified`
  line `copy of the revised instrument of partnership along with the return of income for the assessment year`
  line `relevant to such previous year and all the provisions of this section shall apply accordingly.`
  line `4 [(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, where, in respect of any`
  line `assessment year, there is on the part of a firm any such failure as is mentioned in section 144, the firm`
  line `shall be so assessed that no deduction by way of any payment of interest, salary, bonus, commission or`
  line `remuneration, by whatever name called, made by such firm to any partner of such firm shall be allowed in`
  line `computing the income chargeable under the head "Profits and gains of business or profession" and such`
  line `interest, salary, bonus, commission or remuneration shall not be chargeable to income-tax under clause`
  line `( v ) of section 28.]`
  line `5 [ 185. Assessment when section 184 not complied with. — Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `any other provision of this Act, where a firm does not comply with the provisions of section 184 for any`
  line `assessment year, the firm shall be so assessed that no deduction by way of any payment of interest, salary,`
  line `bonus, commission or remuneration, by whatever name called, made by such firm to any partner of such`
  line `firm shall be allowed in computing the income chargeable under the head “Profits and gains of business`
  line `or profession” and such interest, salary, bonus, commission or remuneration shall not be chargeable to`
  line `income-tax under clause ( v ) of section 28.]]`
  line `1. Section 181 and sub- heading “O.—Liability of State Governments” omitted by Act 26 of 1988, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier sub- heading “A.—Assessment of firms” and sections 182`
  line `and 183 omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 67 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 66, for “sub -heading “B.—Registration of firms” and sections 184, 185 and 86” (w.e.f. 1 -4-`
  line `1993).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 69, for sub-section ( 5 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 70, ibid., for section 185 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
