obj_root_law_sections_632_content:
  string
  line 632
  line `C. — Changes in constitution, succession and dissolution`
  line `187.Change in constitution of a firm. — ( 1 ) Where at the time of making an assessment`
  line `under section 143 or section 144 it is found that a change has occurred in the constitution of a firm, the`
  line `assessment shall be made on the firm as constituted at the time of making the assessment.`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `( 2 ) For the purposes of this section, there is a change in the constitution of the firm —`
  line `( a ) if one or more of the partners cease to be partners or one or more new partners are admitted,`
  line `in such circumstances that one or more of the persons who were partners of the firm before the`
  line `change continue as partner or partners after the change; or`
  line `( b ) where all the partners continue with a change in their respective shares or in the shares of`
  line `some of them:`
  line `2 [Provided that nothing contained in clause ( a ) shall apply to a case where the firm is dissolved on the`
  line `death of any of its partners.]`
  line `188. Succession of one firm by another firm. — Where a firm carrying on a business or profession is`
  line `succeeded by another firm, and the case is not one covered by section 187, separate assessments shall be`
  line `made on the predecessor firm and the successor firm in accordance with the provisions of section 170.`
  line `3 [ 188A. Joint and several liability of partners for tax payable by firm. — Every person who was,`
  line `during the previous year, a partner of a firm, and the legal representative of any such person who is`
  line `deceased, shall be jointly and severally liable along with the firm for the amount of tax, penalty or other`
  line `sum payable by the firm for the assessment year to which such previous year is relevant, and all the`
  line `provisions of this Act, so far as may be, shall apply to the assessment of such tax or imposition or levy of`
  line `such penalty or other sum.]`
  line `189. Firm dissolved or business discontinued. — ( 1 ) Where any business or profession carried on by`
  line `a firm has been discontinued or where a firm is dissolved, the 4 [Assessing Officer] shall make an`
  line `assessment of the total income of the firm as if no such discontinuance or dissolution had taken place, and`
  line `all the provisions of this Act, including the provisions relating to the levy of a penalty or any other sum`
  line `chargeable under any provision of this Act, shall apply, so far as may be, to such assessment.`
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing sub-section, if the 4 [Assessing Officer] or the`
  line `5 [Commissioner (Appeals)] in the course of any proceeding under this Act in respect of any such firm as`
  line `is referred to in that sub-section is satisfied that the firm was guilty of any of the acts specified in Chapter`
  line `XXI, he may impose or direct the imposition of a penalty in accordance with the provisions of that`
  line Chapter.
  line `( 3 ) Every person who was at the time of such discontinuance or dissolution a partner of the firm, and`
  line `the legal representative of any such person who is deceased, shall be jointly and severally liable for the`
  line `amount of tax, penalty or other sum payable, and all the provisions of this Act, so far as may be, shall`
  line `apply to any such assessment or imposition of penalty or other sum.`
  line `6 * * * * *`
  line `1. The proviso omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 67 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993). Earlier the proviso was restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1989) which was omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 69 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. The proviso added by Act 67 of 1984, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-4-1975).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 70 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. The words “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)” omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1 -4- 1998). Earlier “Deputy`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals)” substituted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. The Explanation omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 68 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993). Earlier the Explanation reintroduced by`
  line `Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989) and omitted by Act 4 of 1989, s. 71 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989) which was earlier inserted by`
  line `Act 41 of 1975, s. 52 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975)`
