obj_root_law_sections_633_content:
  string
  line 633
  line `( 4 ) Where such discontinuance or dissolution takes place after any proceedings in respect of an`
  line `assessment year have commenced, the proceedings may be continued against the person referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ) from the stage at which the proceedings stood at the time of such discontinuance or`
  line `dissolution, and all the provisions of this Act shall, so far as may be, apply accordingly.`
  line `( 5 ) Nothing in this section shall affect the provisions of sub-section ( 6 ) of section 159.`
  line `1 [ 189A. Provisions applicable to past assessments of firms. — In relation to the assessment of any`
  line `firm and its partners for the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1992, or any earlier`
  line `assessment year, the provisions of this Chapter as they stood immediately before the 1st day of April,`
  line `1993, shall continue to apply.]`
  line `CHAPTER XVII`
  line `C OLLECTION AND RECOVERY OF TAX`
  line `A. — General`
  line `190. Deductionat source and advance payment. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding that the regular assessment`
  line `in respect of any income is to be made in a later assessment year, the tax on such income shall be payable`
  line `by deduction 2 [or collection] at source 3 [or by advance payment or by payment under sub-section ( 1A )`
  line `of section 192], as the case may be, in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line `( 2 ) Nothing in this section shall prejudice the charge of tax on such income under the provisions of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 4.`
  line `191. Direct payment. — 4 *** In the case of income in respect of which provision is not made under`
  line `this Chapter for deducting income-tax at the time of payment, and in any case where income-tax has not`
  line `been deducted in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter, income-tax shall be payable by the`
  line `assessee direct.`
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `6 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that if any person including the`
  line `principal officer of a company, —`
  line `( a ) who is required to deduct any sum in accordance with the provisions of this Act; or`
  line `( b ) referred to in sub-section ( 1A ) of section 192, being an employer,`
  line `does not deduct, or after so deducting fails to pay, or does not pay, the whole or any part of the tax, as`
  line `required by or under this Act, and where the assessee has also failed to pay such tax directly, then, such`
  line `person shall, without prejudice to any other consequences which he may incur, be deemed to be an`
  line `assessee in default within the meaning of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 201, in respect of such tax.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 69 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993). Earlier section 189A was inserted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 72 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989)`
  line `which was later omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-6-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 70 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `4. The brackets and figure “( 1 )” omitted by Act 10 of 1965, s. 43 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
  line `5. Sub-section ( 2 ) omitted by s. 43, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `6. The Explanation substituted by Act 18 of 2008, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-6-2003). Earlier inserted by 32 of 2003, s. 71 (w.e.f. 1-6-`
  line `2003).`
