obj_root_law_sections_634_content:
  string
  line 634
  line `B. — Deduction at source`
  line `192. Salary. — ( 1 ) Any person responsible for paying any income chargeable under the head`
  line `“Salaries” shall, at the time of payment, deduct income -tax 1 *** on the amount payable at the average rate`
  line `of income-tax 2 *** computed on the basis of the 3 [rates in force] for the financial year in which the`
  line `payment is made, on the estimated income of the assessee under this head for that financial year.`
  line `4 [( 1A ) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section ( 1 ), the person responsible for`
  line `paying any income in the nature of a perquisite which is not provided for by way of monetary payment,`
  line `referred to in clause ( 2 ) of section 17, may pay, at his option, tax on the whole or part of such income`
  line `without making any deduction therefrom at the time when such tax was otherwise deductible under the`
  line `provisions of sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 1B ) For the purpose of paying tax under sub-section ( 1A ), tax shall be determined at the average of`
  line `income-tax computed on the basis of the rates in force for the financial year, on the income chargeable`
  line `under the head “Salaries” including the income referred to in sub -section ( 1A ), and the tax so payable`
  line `shall be construed as if it were, a tax deductible at source, from the income under the head “Salaries” as`
  line `per the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ), and shall be subject to the provisions of this Chapter.]`
  line `5 [( 2 ) Where, during the financial year, an assessee is employed simultaneously under more than one`
  line `employer, or where he has held successively employment under more than one employer, he may furnish`
  line `to the person responsible for making the payment referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) (being one of the said`
  line `employers as the assessee may, having regard to the circumstances of his case, choose), such details of`
  line `the income under the head “Salaries” due or re ceived by him from the other employer or employers, the`
  line `tax deducted at source therefrom and such other particulars, in such form and verified in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed, and thereupon the person responsible for making the payment referred to above shall`
  line `take into account the details so furnished for the purposes of making the deduction under sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 2A ) Where the assessee, being a Government servant or an employee in a 6 [company, co-operative`
  line `society, local authority, university, institution, association or body] is entitled to the relief under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 89, he may furnish to the person responsible for making the payment referred to`
  line `in sub-section ( 1 ), such particulars, in such form and verified in such manner as may be prescribed, and`
  line `thereupon the person responsible as aforesaid shall compute the relief on the basis of such particulars and`
  line `take it into account in making the deduction under sub-section (1).`
  line `7 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, “University” means a University established or`
  line `incorporated by or under a Central, State or Provincial Act, and includes an institution declared under`
  line `section 3 of the University Grants Commission Act, 1956 (3 of 1956), to be a University for the purposes`
  line `of that Act.]`
  line `8 [( 2B ) Where an assessee who receives any income chargeable under the head “Salaries” has, in`
  line `addition, any income chargeable under any other head of income (not being a loss under any such head`
  line `other than the loss under the head “Income from house property”) for the same financial year, he may`
  line `send to the person responsible for making the payment referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) the particulars of —`
  line `( a ) such other income and of any tax deducted thereon under any other provision of this Chapter;`
  line `1. The words “and super tax” omitted by Act 10 of 1965, s. 44 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
  line `2. The words “and average rate of super - tax respectively” omitted by s. 44, ibid (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 19 of 1968, s. 13, for “rates of tax in force” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1968).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 71 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 13 of 1989, s. 21, for “public sector undertaking” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1989).`
  line `7. Ins. by s. 21, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-1989).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 47, for sub-section ( 2B ) (w.e.f. 1-8-1998).`
