obj_root_law_sections_635_content:
  string
  line 635
  line `( b ) the loss, if any, under the head “Income from house property”,`
  line `in such form and verified in such manner as may be prescribed, and thereupon the person responsible as`
  line `aforesaid shall take —`
  line `( i ) such other income and tax, if any, deducted thereon; and`
  line `( ii ) the loss, if any, under the head “Income from house property”,`
  line `also into account for the purposes of making the deduction under sub-section ( 1 ):`
  line `Provided that this sub-section shall not in any case have the effect of reducing the tax deductible`
  line `exce pt where the loss under the head “Income from house property” has been taken into account, from`
  line `income under the head “Salaries” below the amount that would be so deductible if the other income and`
  line `the tax deducted thereon had not been taken into account.]]`
  line `1 [( 2C ) A person responsible for paying any income chargeable under the head “Salaries” shall furnish`
  line `to the person to whom such payment is made a statement giving correct and complete particulars of`
  line `perquisites or profits in lieu of salary provided to him and the value thereof in such form and manner as`
  line `may be prescribed.]`
  line `2 [( 2D ) The person responsible for making the payment referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall, for the`
  line `purposes of estimating income of the assessee or computing tax deductible under sub-section ( 1 ), obtain`
  line `from the assessee the evidence or proof or particulars of prescribed claims (including claim for set-off of`
  line `loss) under the provisions of the Act in such form and manner as may be prescribed.]`
  line `( 3 ) The person responsible for making the payment referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) 3 [or sub-section`
  line `( 1A )] 4 [or sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-section ( 2A ) or sub-section ( 2B )] may, at the time of making any`
  line `deduction, increase or reduce the amount to be deducted under this section for the purpose of adjusting`
  line `any excess or deficiency arising out of any previous deduction or failure to deduct during the financial`
  line year.
  line `( 4 ) The trustees of a recognised provident fund, or any person authorised by the regulations of the`
  line `fund to make payment of accumulated balances due to employees, shall, in cases where sub-rule ( 1 ) of`
  line `rule 9 of Part A of the Fourth Schedule applies, at the time an accumulated balance due to an employee is`
  line `paid, make therefrom the deduction provided in rule 10 of Part A of the Fourth Schedule.`
  line `( 5 ) Where any contribution made by an employer, including interest on such contributions, if any, in`
  line `an approved superannuation fund is paid to the employee, 5 [tax] on the amount so paid shall be deducted`
  line `by the trustees of the fund to the extent provided in rule 6 of Part B of the Fourth Schedule.`
  line `( 6 ) For the purposes of deduction of tax on salary payable in foreign currency, the value in rupees of`
  line `such salary shall be calculated at the prescribedrate of exchange.`
