  line 636
  line `person authorised under the scheme to make payment of accumulated balance due to employees, shall, in`
  line `a case where the accumulated balance due to an employee participating in a recognised provident fund is`
  line `includible in his total income owing to the provisions of rule 8 of Part A of the Fourth Schedule not being`
  line `applicable, at the time of payment of the accumulated balance due to the employee, deduct income-tax`
  line `thereon at the rate of ten per cent:`
  line `Provided that no deduction under this section shall be made where the amount of such payment or, as`
  line `the case may be, the aggregate amount of such payment to the payee is less than 1 [fifty thousand rupees]:`
  line `Provided further that any person entitled to receive any amount on which tax is deductible under this`
  line `section shall furnish his Permanent Account Number to the person responsible for deducting such tax,`
  line `failing which tax shall be deducted at the maximum marginal rate.]`
  line `193. Interest on securities. — 2 [The person responsible for paying to a residentany income] 3 [by way`
