  line `declaration in writing before the person responsible for paying the interest that the total nominal value`
  line `of the 6½ per cent Gold Bonds, 1977, or, as the case may be, the 7 per cent. Gold Bonds, 1980, held`
  line `by him (including such bonds, if any, held on his behalf by any other person) did not in either case`
  line `exceed ten thousand rupees at any time during the period to which the interest relates;]`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `2 [( iv ) any interest payable on any security of the Central Government or a State Government:]`
  line `3 [Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall apply to the interest exceeding rupees ten`
  line `thousand payable on 8% Savings (Taxable) Bonds, 2003 4 [or 7.75% Savings (Taxable) Bonds, 2018]`
  line `during the financial year;]`
  line `5 [( v ) any interest payable to an individual or a Hindu undivided family, who is resident in India,`
  line `on any debenture issued by a company in which the public are substantially interested, if —`
  line `( a ) the amount of interest or, as the case may be, the aggregate amount of such interest paid`
  line `or likely to be paid on such debenture during the financial year by the company to such individual`
  line `or Hindu undivided family does not exceed five thousand rupees; and`
  line `( b ) such interest is paid by the company by an account payee cheque;]`
  line `6 [( vi ) any interest payable to the Life Insurance Corporation of India established under the Life`
  line `Insurance Corporation Act, 1956 (31 of 1956), in respect of any securities owned by it or in which it`
  line `has full beneficial interest; or`
  line `( vii ) any interest payable to the General Insurance Corporation of India (hereafter in this clause`
  line `referred to as the Corporation) or to any of the four companies (hereafter in this clause referred to as`
  line `such company), formed by virtue of the schemes framed under sub-section (1) of section 16 of the`
  line `General Insurance Business (Nationalisation) Act, 1972 (57 of 1972), in respect of any securities`
  line `owned by the Corporation or such company or in which the Corporation or such company has full`
  line `beneficial interest; or`
  line `( viii ) any interest payable to any other insurer in respect of any securities owned by it or in which`
  line `it has full beneficial interest;]`
  line `7 [( ix ) any interest payable on any security issued by a company, where such security is in`
  line `dematerialised form and is listed on a recognised stock exchange in India in accordance with the`
  line `Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956) and the rules made thereunder.]`
  line `8 [ Explanation 9 ***. — For the purposes of this section, where any income by way of interest on`
  line `securities is credited to any account, whether called “Interest payable account” or “Suspense account” or`
  line `by any other name, in the books of account of the person liable to pay such income, such crediting shall`
  line `be deemed to be credit of such income to the account of the payee and the provisions of this section shall`
  line `apply accordingly.]`
  line `10 * * * * *`
