obj_root_law_sections_638_content:
  string
  line 638
  line `194. Dividends. — The principal officer of an Indian company or a company which has made the`
  line `prescribed arrangements for the declaration and payment of dividends (including dividends on preference`
  line `shares) within India, shall, before making any payment in cash or before issuing any cheque or warrant in`
  line `respect of any dividend or before making any distribution or payment to a shareholder, 1 [who is resident`
  line `in India,] of any dividend within the meaning of sub-clause ( a ) or sub-clause ( b ) or sub-clause ( c ) or`
  line `sub-clause ( d ) or sub-clause ( e ) of clause ( 22 ) of section 2, deduct from the amount of such dividend,`
  line `income-tax 2 *** at the rates in force:`
  line `3 [Provided that no such deduction shall be made in the case of a shareholder, being an individual, if —`
  line `( a ) the dividend is paid by the company by an account payee cheque; and`
  line `( b ) the amount of such dividend or, as the case may be, the aggregate of the amounts of such`
  line `dividend distributed or paid or likely to be distributed or paid during the financial year by the`
  line `company to the shareholder, does not exceed 4 [two thousand five hundred rupees]:`
  line `Provided further that the provisions of this section shall not apply to such income credited or paid`
  line `to —`
  line `( a ) the Life Insurance Corporation of India established under the Life Insurance Corporation`
  line `Act, 1956 (31 of 1956), in respect of any shares owned by it or in which it has full beneficial`
  line interest;
  line `( b ) the General Insurance Corporation of India (hereafter in this proviso referred to as the`
  line `Corporation) or to any of the four companies (hereafter in this proviso referred to as such`
  line `company), formed by virtue of the schemes framed under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 16 of the`
  line `General Insurance Business (Nationalisation) Act, 1972 (57 of 1972), in respect of any shares`
  line `owned by the Corporation or such company or in which the Corporation or such company has full`
  line `beneficial interest;`
  line `( c ) any other insurer in respect of any shares owned by it or in which it has full beneficial`
  line `interest:]`
  line `5 [Provided also that no such deduction shall be made in respect of any dividends referred to`
  line `in section 115-O.]`
  line `6 [ 194A. Interest other than “Interest on securities”. — ( 1 ) Any person, not being an individual or a`
  line `Hindu undivided family, who is responsible for paying to a resident any income by way of interest other`
  line `than income by way of interest on securities, shall, at the time of credit of such income to the account of`
  line `the payee or at the time of payment thereof in cash or by issue of a cheque or draft or by any other mode,`
  line `whichever is earlier, deduct income-tax thereon at the rates in force:`
  line `7 [Provided that an individual or a Hindu undivided family, whose total sales, gross receipts or`
  line `turnover from the business or profession carried on by him exceed the monetary limits specified under`
  line `clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of section 44AB during the financial year immediately preceding the financial`
  line `year in which such interest is credited or paid, shall be liable to deduct income-tax under this section.]`
  line `8 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, where any income by way of interest as aforesaid is`
  line `cred ited to any account, whether called “Interest payable account” or “Suspense account” or by any other`
  line `name, in the books of account of the person liable to pay such income, such crediting shall be deemed to`
  line `be credit of such income to the account of the payee and the provisions of this section shall apply`
  line accordingly.]
  line `1. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 51 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line `2. The words “and super - tax” omitted by Act 10 of 1965 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 73, for the first and second provisos (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `4.Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 73, for “one thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1-8-2002).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 73, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-4-1967).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 74 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
