  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_642_footnotes
  sourcePage 642
obj_root_law_sections_642_content:
  string
  line 642
  line `1 [194B. Winnings from lottery or crossword puzzle. ―The person responsible for paying to any`
  line `person any income by way of winnings from any lottery or crossword puzzle 2 [or card game and other`
  line `game of any sort] in an amount exceeding 3 [ten thousand rupees] shall, at the time of payment thereof,`
  line `deduct income-tax thereon at the rates in force:`
  line `4 * * * * *]`
  line `5 [ 6 [Providedthat] in a case where the winnings are wholly in kind or partly in cash and partly in kind`
  line `but the part in cash is not sufficient to meet the liability of deduction of tax in respect of whole of the`
  line `winnings, the person responsible for paying shall, before releasing the winnings, ensure that tax has been`
  line `paid in respect of the winnings.]`
  line `7 [ 194BB. Winnings from horse race. ―Any person, being a bookmaker or a person to whom a`
  line `licence has been granted by the Government under any law for the time being in force for horse racing in`
  line `any race course or for arranging for wagering or betting in any race course, who is responsible for paying`
  line `to any person any income by way of winnings from any horse race in an amount exceeding 8 [ten thousand`
  line `rupees] shall, at the time of payment thereof, deduct income-tax thereon at the rates in force.`
  line `4 * * * * *]`
  line `9 [ 194C. Payments to contractors. — ( 1 ) Any person responsible for paying any sum to any resident`
  line `(hereafter in this section referred to as the contractor) for carrying out any work (including supply of`
  line `labour for carrying out any work) in pursuance of a contract between the contractor and a specified person`
  line `shall, at the time of credit of such sum to the account of the contractor or at the time of payment thereof in`
  line `cash or by issue of a cheque or draft or by any other mode, whichever is earlier, deduct an amount equal`
  line `to —`
  line `( i ) one per cent where the payment is being made or credit is being given to an individual or a`
  line `Hindu undivided family;`
  line `( ii ) two per cent where the payment is being made or credit is being given to a person other than`
  line `an individual or a Hindu undivided family,`
  line `of such sum as income-tax on income comprised therein.`
  line `( 2 ) Where any sum referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) is credited to any account, whether called “Suspense`
  line `account” or by any other name, in the books of account of the person liable to pay such income, such`
  line `crediting shall be deemed to be credit of such income to the account of the payee and the provisions of`
  line `this section shall apply accordingly.`
  line `( 3 ) Where any sum is paid or credited for carrying out any work mentioned in sub-clause ( e ) of clause`
  line `( iv ) of the Explanation, tax shall be deducted at source —`
  line `( i ) on the invoice value excluding the value of material, if such value is mentioned separately in`
  line `the invoice; or`
  line `( ii ) on the whole of the invoice value, if the value of material is not mentioned separately in the`
  line invoice.
  line `1. Ins. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1-4-1975).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 70 (w.e.f. 1-6-2001).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 35, for “five thousands rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2010). Earlier substituted by Act 26 of 1986, s.`
  line `30, for “one thousands rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1986).`
  line `4. The proviso omitted by Act 27 of 1999, s. 70 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 48 (w.e.f. 1-6-1997).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 70, “Provided futher that” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2000).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 19 of 1978, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-1978).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 73, for “five thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2016).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 61, for section 194C (w.e.f. 1-10-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_642_footnotes:
