obj_root_law_sections_643_content:
  string
  line 643
  line `( 4 ) No individual or Hindu undivided family shall be liable to deduct income-tax on the sum credited`
  line `or paid to the account of the contractor where such sum is credited or paid exclusively for personal`
  line `purposes of such individual or any member of Hindu undivided family.`
  line `( 5 ) No deduction shall be made from the amount of any sum credited or paid or likely to be credited`
  line `or paid to the account of, or to, the contractor, if such sum does not exceed 1 [thirty thousand rupees]:`
  line `Provided that where the aggregate of the amounts of such sums credited or paid or likely to be`
  line `credited or paid during the financial year exceeds 2 [ one lakh rupees ], the person responsible for paying`
  line `such sums referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be liable to deduct income-tax under this section.`
  line `( 6 ) No deduction shall be made from any sum credited or paid or likely to be credited or paid during`
  line `the previous year to the account of a contractor during the course of business of plying, hiring or leasing`
  line `goods carriages, 3 [where such contractor owns ten or less goods carriages at any time during the previous`
  line `year and furnishes a declaration to that effect along with] his Permanent Account Number, to the person`
  line `paying or crediting such sum.`
  line `( 7 ) The person responsible for paying or crediting any sum to the person referred to in sub-section ( 6 )`
  line `shall furnish, to the prescribed income-tax authority or the person authorised by it, such particulars, in`
  line `such form and within such time as may be prescribed.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “specified person” shall mean,—`
  line `( a ) the Central Government or any State Government; or`
  line `( b ) any local authority; or`
  line `( c ) any corporation established by or under a Central, State or Provincial Act; or`
  line `( d ) any company; or`
  line `( e ) any co-operative society; or`
  line `( f ) any authority, constituted in India by or under any law, engaged either for the purpose of`
  line `dealing with and satisfying the need for housing accommodation or for the purpose of planning,`
  line `development or improvement of cities, towns and villages, or for both; or`
  line `( g ) any society registered under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860) or under`
  line `any law corresponding to that Act in force in any part of India; or`
  line `( h ) any trust; or`
  line `( i ) any university established or incorporated by or under a Central, State or Provincial Act`
  line `and an institution declared to be a university under section 3 of the University Grants`
  line `Commission Act, 1956 (3 of 1956); or`
  line `( j ) any Government of a foreign State or a foreign enterprise or any association or body`
  line `established outside India; or`
  line `( k ) any firm; or`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 37, for “twenty thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2010).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 74, for “seventy - five thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2016). Earlier the quoted words were`
  line `sub stituted for “fifty thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2010).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 44, for “on furnishing of” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2015).`
