obj_root_law_sections_644_content:
  string
  line 644
  line `( l ) any person, being an individual or a Hindu undivided family or an association of persons`
  line `or a body of individuals, if such person, —`
  line `( A ) does not fall under any of the preceding sub-clauses; and`
  line `( B ) is liable to audit of accounts under clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of section 44AB during the`
  line `financial year immediately preceding the financial year in which such sum is credited or paid`
  line `to the account of the contractor;`
  line `( ii ) “goods carriage” shall have the meaning assigned to it in the Explanation to sub-section ( 7 )`
  line `of section 44AE;`
  line `( iii ) “contract” shall include sub -contract;`
  line `( iv ) “work” shall include—`
  line `( a ) advertising;`
  line `( b ) broadcasting and telecasting including production of programmes for such broadcasting`
  line `or telecasting;`
  line `( c ) carriage of goods or passengers by any mode of transport other than by railways;`
  line `( d ) catering;`
  line `( e ) manufacturing or supplying a product according to the requirement or specification of a`
  line `customer by using material purchased from such customer,`
  line `but does not include manufacturing or supplying a product according to the requirement or specification`
  line `of a customer by using material purchased from a person, other than such customer.]`
  line `1 [ 194D. Insurance commission. — Any person responsible for paying to a resident any income by`
  line `way of remuneration or reward, whether by way of commission or otherwise, for soliciting or procuring`
  line `insurance business (including business relating to the continuance, renewal or revival of policies of`
  line `insurance) shall, at the time of credit of such income to the account of the payee or at the time of payment`
  line `thereof in cash or by issue of a cheque or draft or by any other mode, whichever is earlier, deduct income-`
  line `tax thereon at the rates in force:`
  line `Provided that no deduction shall be made under this section from any such income credited or paid`
  line `before the 1st day of June, 1973:]`
  line `2 [Provided further that no deduction shall be made under this section in a case where the amount of`
  line `such income or, as the case may be, the aggregate of the amounts of such income credited or paid or`
  line `likely to be credited or paid during the financial year to the account of, or to, the payee, does not`
  line `exceed 3 [fifteen thousand rupees].]`
  line `4 [ 194DA. Payment in respect of life insurance policy. — Any person responsible for paying to a`
  line `resident any sum under a life insurance policy, including the sum allocated by way of bonus on such`
  line `policy, other than the amount not includible in the total income under clause ( 10D ) of section 10, shall, at`
  line `the time of payment thereof, deduct income-tax thereon at the rate of 5 [ one per cent. ]:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1973, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 48 (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 75, for “twenty thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2016). Earlier the quoted words were substituted`
  line `by Act 14 of 2010, s. 38, for “five thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2010).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 57 (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 28 of 201 6, s. 76, for “two per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2016).`
