obj_root_law_sections_645_content:
  string
  line 645
  line `Provided that no deduction under this section shall be made where the amount of such payment or, as`
  line `the case may be, the aggregate amount of such payments to the payee during the financial year is less than`
  line `one hundred thousand rupees.]`
  line `1 [ 194E. Payments to non-resident sportsmen or sports associations. — Where any income referred`
  line `to in section 115BBA is payable to a non-resident sportsman (including an athlete) 2 [or an entertainer]`
  line `who is not a citizen of India or a non-resident sports association or institution, the person responsible for`
  line `making the payment shall, at the time of credit of such income to the account of the payee or at the time`
  line `of payment thereof in cash or by issue of a cheque or draft or by any other mode, whichever is earlier,`
  line `deduct income-tax thereon at the rate of 3 [twenty per cent.].]`
  line `4 [ 194EE. Payments in respect of deposits under National Savings Scheme, etc. — The person`
  line `responsible for paying to any person any amount referred to in clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section`
  line `80CCA shall, at the time of payment thereof, deduct income-tax thereon at the rate of 5 [ ten per cent. ]:`
  line `Provided that no deduction shall be made under this section where the amount of such payment or, as`
  line `the case may be, the aggregate amount of such payments to the payee during the financial year is less than`
  line `two thousand five hundred rupees:`
  line `Provided further that nothing contained in this section shall apply to the payment of the said amount`
  line `to the heirs of the assessee.]`
  line `6 [ 194F. Payments on account of repurchase of units by Mutual Fund or Unit Trust of India. —`
  line `The person responsible for paying to any person any amount referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) of section`
  line `80CCB shall, at the time of payment thereof, deduct income-tax thereon at the rate of twenty per cent.]`
  line `7 [ 194G. Commission, etc., on the sale of lottery tickets. — 8 [( 1 )] Any person who is responsible for`
  line `paying, on or after the 1st day of October, 1991 to any person, who is or has been stocking, distributing,`
  line `purchasing or selling lottery tickets, any income by way of commission, remuneration or prize (by`
  line `whatever name called) on such tickets in an amount exceeding 9 [fifteen thousand rupees ] shall, at the time`
  line `of credit of such income to the account of the payee or at the time of payment of such income in cash or`
  line `by the issue of a cheque or draft or by any other mode, whichever is earlier, deduct income-tax thereon at`
  line `the rate of 10 [ five per cent. ].]`
  line `11 * * * * *`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, where any income is credited to any account, whether`
  line `called "Suspense Account" or by any other name, in the books of account of the person liable to pay such`
  line `income, such crediting shall be deemed to be credit of such income to the account of the payee and the`
  line `provisions of this section shall apply accordingly.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 36 of 1989, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-11-1989). Earlier section 194D was omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 31(w.e.f. 1-4-`
  line `1988) which was inserted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 74 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 73 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 73, ibid., for “ten per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 54 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 77, for “twenty per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2016).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 55 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line `8. Section 73 renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 18 of 1992, s. 73 (w.e.f. 1-6-1992).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 78, for “one thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2016).`
  line `10. Subs. by s. 78, ibid., for “ten per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2016).`
  line `11. Sub-sections ( 2 ) and ( 3 ) omitted by Act 32 of 2003, s. 76 (w.e.f. 1-6-2003). Earlier sub-sections ( 2 ) and ( 3 ) were inserted`
  line `by Act 18 of 1992, s. 73 (w.e.f. 1-6-1992).`
