obj_root_law_sections_646_content:
  string
  line 646
  line `1 [194H. Commission or brokerage. — Any person, not being an individual or a Hindu undivided`
  line `family, who is responsible for paying, on or after the 1st day of June, 2001, to a resident, any income by`
  line `way of commission (not being insurance commission referred to in section 194D) or brokerage, shall, at`
  line `the time of credit of such income to the account of the payee or at the time of payment of such income in`
  line `cash or by the issue of a cheque or draft or by any other mode, whichever is earlier, deduct income-tax`
  line `thereon at the rate of 2 [five per cent.]:`
  line `Provided that no deduction shall be made under this section in a case where the amount of such`
  line `income or, as the case may be, the aggregate of the amounts of such income credited or paid or likely to`
  line `be credited or paid during the financial year to the account of, or to, the payee, does not exceed 3 [fifteen`
  line `thousand rupees]:`
  line `4 [Provided further that an individual or a Hindu undivided family, whose total sales, gross receipts or`
  line `turnover from the business or profession carried on by him exceed the monetary limits specified under`
  line `clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of section 44AB during the financial year immediately preceding the financial`
  line `year in which such commission or brokerage is credited or paid, shall be liable to deduct income-tax`
  line `under this section:]`
  line `5 [Provided also that no deduction shall be made under this section on any commission or brokerage`
  line `payable by Bharat Sanchar Nigam Limited or Mahanagar Telephone Nigam Limited to their public call`
  line `office franchisees.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “commission or brokerage” includes any payment received or receivable, directly or indirectly,`
  line `by a person acting on behalf of another person for services rendered (not being professional services)`
  line `or for any services in the course of buying or selling of goods or in relation to any transaction relating`
  line `to any asset, valuable article or thing, not being securities;`
  line `( ii ) the expression “professional services” means services rendered by a person in the course of`
  line `carrying on a legal, medical, engineering or architectural profession or the profession of accountancy`
  line `or technical consultancy or interior decoration or such other profession as is notified by the Board for`
  line `the purposes of section 44AA;`
  line `( iii ) the expression “securities” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( h ) of section 2 of`
  line `the Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956);`
  line `( iv ) where any income is credited to any account, whether called “Suspense account” or by any`
  line `other name, in the books of account of the person liable to pay such income, such crediting shall be`
  line `deemed to be credit of such income to the account of the payee and the provisions of this section shall`
  line `apply accordingly.]`
  line `1. Section 194H reinserted by Act 14 of 2001, s. 71 (w.e.f. 1-6-2001). Earlier section 194H was omitted by Act 27 of 1999,`
  line `s. 72 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000). Amended by Act 18 of 1992, s. 74 (w.e.f. 1-6-1992) and prior its omission section 194H was`
  line `inserted by Act 49 of 1991, s. 55 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 79, for “ten per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2016).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 79, ibid., for “five thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2016).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 76 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 55 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
