obj_root_law_sections_647_content:
  string
  line 647
  line `1 [ 194-I. Rent. — 2 [Any person, not being an individual or a Hindu undivided family, who is`
  line `responsible for paying to a resident] any income by way of rent, shall, at the time of credit of such income`
  line `to the account of the payee or at the time of payment thereof in cash or by the issue of a cheque or draft or`
  line `by any other mode, whichever is earlier, 3 [deduct income-tax thereon at the rate of —`
  line `4 [( a ) two per cent. for the use of any machinery or plant or equipment; and`
  line `( b ) ten per cent. for the use of any land or building (including factory building) or land`
  line `appurtenant to a building (including factory building) or furniture or fittings:]]`
  line `Provided that no deduction shall be made under this section where the amount of such income or,`
  line `as the case may be, the aggregate of the amounts of such income credited or paid or likely to be`
  line `credited or paid during the financial year by the aforesaid person to the account of, or to, the payee,`
  line `does not exceed 5 [two hundred and forty thousand rupees]:`
  line `6 [Provided further that an individual or a Hindu undivided family, whose total sales, gross`
  line `receipts or turnover from the business or profession carried on by him exceed the monetary limits`
  line `specified under clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of section 44AB during the financial year immediately`
  line `preceding the financial year in which such income by way of rent is credited or paid, shall be liable to`
  line `deduct income-tax under this section:]`
  line `7 [Provided also that no deduction shall be made under this section where the income by way of`
  line `rent is credited or paid to a business trust, being a real estate investment trust, in respect of any real`
  line `estate asset, referred to in clause ( 23FCA ) of section 10, owned directly by such business trust.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `8 [( i ) “rent” means any payment, by whatever name called, under any lease, su b-lease, tenancy or`
  line `any other agreement or arrangement for the use of (either separately or together) any, —`
  line `( a ) land; or`
  line `( b ) building (including factory building); or`
  line `( c ) land appurtenant to a building (including factory building); or`
  line `( d ) machinery; or`
  line `( e ) plant; or`
  line `( f ) equipment; or`
  line `( g ) furniture; or`
  line `( h ) fittings,`
  line `whether or not any or all of the above are owned by the payee;]`
  line `( ii ) where any income is credited to any account, whether called “Suspense account” or by any`
  line `other name, in the books of account of the person liable to pay such income, such crediting shall be`
  line `deemed to be credit of such income to the account of the payee and the provisions of this section shall`
  line `apply accordingly.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-6-1994).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 77, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 35, for “deduct income- tax thereon at the rate of twenty per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -7-1995).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 62, for clauses ( a ), ( b ) and ( c ) (w.e.f. 1-10-2009).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 10, for “one hundred eighty thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2019). Earlier it was substituted by`
  line `Act 14 of 2010, s. 40, for “one hundred and twenty thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2010).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 77 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 15, for clause ( i ) (w.e.f. 13-7-2006).`
