  content obj_root_law_sections_648_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_648_footnotes
  sourcePage 648
obj_root_law_sections_648_content:
  string
  line 648
  line `1 [194-IA. Payment on transfer of certain immovable property other than agricultural land — ( 1 )`
  line `Any person, being a transferee, responsible for paying (other than the person referred to in section`
  line `194LA) to a resident transferor any sum by way of consideration for transfer of any immovable property`
  line `(other than agricultural land), shall, at the time of credit of such sum to the account of the transferor or at`
  line `the time of payment of such sum in cash or by issue of a cheque or draft or by any other mode, whichever`
  line `is earlier, deduct an amount equal to one per cent. of such sum as income-tax thereon.`
  line `( 2 ) No deduction under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be made where the consideration for the transfer of an`
  line `immovable property is less than fifty lakh rupees.`
  line `( 3 ) The provisions of section 203A shall not apply to a person required to deduct tax in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of this section.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “agricultural land” means agricultural land in India, not being a land situate in any area`
  line `referred to in items ( a ) and ( b ) of sub-clause ( iii ) of clause ( 14 ) of section 2;`
  line `( b ) ”immovable property” means any land (other than agricultural land) or any building or part of`
  line `a building.]`
  line `2 [194-IB. Payment of rent by certain individuals or Hindu undivided family. — ( 1 ) Any person,`
  line `being an individual or a Hindu undivided family (other than those referred to in the second proviso to`
  line `section 194-I), responsible for paying to a resident any income by way of rent exceeding fifty thousand`
  line `rupees for a month or part of a month during the previous year, shall deduct an amount equal to five per`
  line `cent. of such income as income-tax thereon.`
  line `( 2 ) The income-tax referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be deducted on such income at the time of`
  line `credit of rent, for the last month of the previous year or the last month of tenancy, if the property is`
  line `vacated during the year, as the case may be, to the account of the payee or at the time of payment thereof`
  line `in cash or by issue of a cheque or draft or by any other mode, whichever is earlier.`
  line `( 3 ) The provisions of section 203A shall not apply to a person required to deduct tax in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of this section.`
  line `( 4 ) In a case where the tax is required to be deducted as per the provisions of section 206AA, such`
  line `deduction shall not exceed the amount of rent payable for the last month of the previous year or the last`
  line `month of the tenancy, as the case may be.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, “rent” means any payment, by whatever name called,`
  line `under any lease, sub-lease, tenancy or any other agreement or arrangement for the use of any land or`
  line `building or both.]`
  line `3 [ 194-IC. Payment under specified agreement. — Notwithstanding anything contained in section`
  line `194-IA, any person responsible for paying to a resident any sum by way of consideration, not being`
  line `consideration in kind, under the agreement referred to in sub-section ( 5A ) of section 45, shall at the time`
  line `of credit of such sum to the account of the payee or at the time of payment thereof in cash or by issue of a`
  line `cheque or draft or by any other mode, whichever is earlier, deduct an amount equal to ten per cent. of`
  line `such sum as income-tax thereon.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 46 (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 64 (w.e.f. 1-6-2017).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 65, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
