obj_root_law_sections_649_content:
  string
  line 649
  line `1 [194J. Fees for professional or technical services. — ( 1 ) Any person, not being an individual or a`
  line `Hindu undivided family, who is responsible for paying to a resident any sum by way of —`
  line `( a ) fees for professional services, or`
  line `( b ) fees for technical services, 2 [or]`
  line `3 [( ba ) any remuneration or fees or commission by whatever name called, other than those on`
  line `which tax is deductible under section 192, to a director of a company, or]`
  line `2 [( c ) royalty, or`
  line `( d ) any sum referred to in clause ( va ) of section 28,]`
  line `shall, at the time of credit of such sum to the account of the payee or at the time of payment thereof in`
  line `cash or by issue of a cheque or draft or by any other mode, whichever is earlier, deduct an amount equal`
  line `to 4 [ten per cent.] of such sum as income-tax on income comprised therein:`
  line `Provided that no deduction shall be made under this section —`
  line `( A ) from any sums as aforesaid credited or paid before the 1st day of July, 1995; or`
  line `( B ) where the amount of such sum or, as the case may be, the aggregate of the amounts of such`
  line `sums credited or paid or likely to be credited or paid during the financial year by the aforesaid person`
  line `to the account of, or to, the payee, does not exceed —`
  line `( i ) 5 [thirty thousand rupees], in the case of fees for professional services referred to in clause`
  line `( a ), or`
  line `( ii ) 5 [thirty thousand rupees], in the case of fees for technical services referred to in 6 [clause`
  line `( b ), or]`
  line `2 [( iii ) 5 [thirty thousand rupees], in the case of royalty referred to in clause ( c ), or`
  line `( iv ) 5 [thirty thousand rupees], in the case of sum referred to in clause ( d ):]`
  line `7 [Provided further that an individual or a Hindu undivided family, whose total sales, gross`
  line `receipts or turnover from the business or profession carried on by him exceed the monetary limits`
  line `specified under clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of section 44AB during the financial year immediately`
  line `preceding the financial year in which such sum by way of fees for professional services or`
  line `technical services is credited or paid, shall be liable to deduct income-tax under this section:]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-7-1995).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 16 (w.e.f. 13-7-2006).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 74 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 57, for “five per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2007).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 41, for “twenty thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2010).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 16,for “clause ( b ):” (w.e.f. 13 -7-2006).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 78 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
