obj_root_law_sections_650_content:
  string
  line 650
  line `1 [Provided also that no individual or a Hindu undivided family referred to in the second`
  line `proviso shall be liable to deduct income-tax on the sum by way of fees for professional services`
  line `incase such sum is credited or paid exclusively for personal purposes of such individual or any`
  line `member of Hindu undivided family:]`
  line `2 [Provided also that the provisions of this section shall have effect, as if for the words “ten`
  line `per cent.”, the words “two per cent.” had been substituted in the case of a payee, engaged only in`
  line `the business of operation of call centre.]`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “professional services” means services rendered by a person in the course of carrying on legal,`
  line `medical, engineering or architectural profession or the profession of accountancy or technical`
  line `consultancy or interior decoration or advertising or such other profession as is notified by the Board`
  line `for the purposes of section 44AA or of this section;`
  line `( b ) “fees for technical services” shall ha ve the same meaning as in Explanation 2 to clause ( vii ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 9;`
  line `4 [( ba ) “royalty” shall have the same meaning as in Explanation 2 to clause ( vi ) of sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 9;]`
  line `( c ) where any sum referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) is credited to any account, whether called`
  line `“suspense account” or by any other name, in the books of account of the person liable to pay such`
  line `sum, such crediting shall be deemed to be credit of such sum to the account of the payee and the`
  line `provisions of this section shall apply accordingly.`
  line `194K. [Income in respect of units.] — Omitted by the Finance Act, 2016 (28 of 2016), s. 80`
  line `( w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `194L. [ Payment of compensation on acquisition of capital asset.] — Omitted by s. 80, ibid.`
  line `( w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `5 [194LA. Payment of compensation on acquisition of certain immovable property. — Any person`
  line `responsible for paying to a resident any sum, being in the nature of compensation or the enhanced`
  line `compensation or the consideration or the enhanced consideration on account of compulsory acquisition,`
  line `under any law for the time being in force, of any immovable property (other than agricultural land), shall,`
  line `at the time of payment of such sum in cash or by issue of a cheque or draft or by any other mode,`
  line `whichever is earlier, deduct an amount equal to ten per cent of such sum as income-tax thereon:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 78 (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 66 (w.e.f. 1-6-2017).`
  line `3. Subs-section ( 2 ) and ( 3 ) omitted by Act 32 of 2003, s. 78 (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 16 (w.e.f. 13-7-2006).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 38 (w.e.f. 1-10-2004).`
