obj_root_law_sections_651_content:
  string
  line 651
  line `Provided that no deduction shall be made under this section where the amount of such payment or, as`
  line `the case may be, the aggregate amount of such payments to a resident during the financial year does not`
  line `exceed 1 [two lakh and fifty thousand rupees]:`
  line `2 [ Provided further that no deduction shall be made under this section where such payment is made in`
  line `respect of any award or agreement which has been exempted from levy of income-tax under section 96 of`
  line `the Right to Fair Compensation and Transparency in Land Acquisition, Rehabilitation and Resettlement`
  line `Act, 2013 (30 of 2013). ]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “agricultural land” means agricultural land in India including land situate in any area referred`
  line `to in items ( a ) and ( b ) of sub-clause ( iii ) of clause ( 14 ) of section 2;`
  line `( ii ) “immovable property” means any land (other than agricultural land) or any building or part`
  line `of a building.]`
  line `3 [ 194LB. Income by way of interest from infrastructure debt fund. — Where any income by way`
  line `of interest is payable to a non-resident, not being a company, or to a foreign company, by an`
  line `infrastructure debt fund referred to in clause ( 47 ) of section 10, the person responsible for making the`
  line `payment shall, at the time of credit of such income to the account of the payee or at the time of payment`
  line `thereof in cash or by issue of a cheque or draft or by any other mode, whichever is earlier, deduct income-`
  line `tax thereon at the rate of five per cent.]`
  line `4 [ 194LBA.Certain income from units of a business trust. — ( 1 ) Where any distributed income`
  line `referred to in section 115UA, being of the nature referred to 5 [in sub-clause ( a ) of clause ( 23FC )] 6 [or`
  line `clause ( 23FCA )] of section 10, is payable by a business trust to its unit holder being a resident, the person`
  line `responsible for making the payment shall at the time of credit of such payment to the account of the payee`
  line `or at the time of payment thereof in cash or by the issue of a cheque or draft or by any other mode,`
  line `whichever is earlier, deduct income-tax thereon at the rate of ten per cent.`
  line `( 2 ) Where any distributed income referred to in section 115UA, being of the nature referred to`
  line `5 [in sub-clause ( a ) of clause ( 23FC )] of section 10, is payable by a business trust to its unit holder, 7 [being`
  line `a non-resident (not being a company)] or a foreign company, the person responsible for making the`
  line `payment shall at the time of credit of such payment to the account of the payee or at the time of payment`
  line `thereof in cash or by the issue of a cheque or draft or by any other mode, whichever is earlier, deduct`
  line `income-tax thereon at the rate of five per cent.]`
  line `6 [( 3 ) Where anydistributed income referred to in section 115UA, being of the nature referred to in`
  line `clause ( 23FCA ) of section 10, is payable by a business trust to its unit holder, being a non-resident (not`
  line `being a company), or a foreign company, the person responsible for making the payment shall at the time`
  line `of credit of such payment to the account of the payee or at the time of payment thereof in cash or by the`
  line `issue of a cheque or draft or by any other mode, whichever is earlier, deduct income-tax thereon at the`
  line `rates in force.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 81, for “two hundred thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2016).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 67 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1-6-2011).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 58 (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 82, for “in clause ( 23FC )” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2016).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 46 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 46, ibid., for “being a non - resident, not being a company” (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
