obj_root_law_sections_652_content:
  string
  line 652
  line `1 [ 194LBB. Income in respect of units of investment fund. — Where any income, other than that`
  line `proportion of income which is of the same nature as income referred to in clause ( 23FBB ) of section 10,`
  line `is payable to a unit holder in respect of units of an investment fund specified in clause ( a ) of`
  line `the Explanation 1 to section 115UB, the person responsible for making the payment shall, at the time of`
  line `credit of such income to the account of payee or at the time of payment thereof in cash or by issue of a`
  line `cheque or draft or by any other mode, whichever is earlier, 2 [deduct income-tax thereon, —`
  line `( i ) at the rate of ten per cent, where the payee is a resident;`
  line `( ii ) at the rates in force, where the payee is a non-resident (not being a company) or a foreign`
  line `company:`
  line `Provided that where the payee is a non-resident (not being a company) or a foreign company, no`
  line `deduction shall be made in respect of any income that is not chargeable to tax under the provisions of the`
  line Act.]
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “unit” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( c ) of the Explanation 1 to`
  line `section 115UB;`
  line `( b ) where any income as aforesaid is credited to any account, whether called “suspense account”`
  line `or by any other name, in the books of account of the person liable to pay such income, such crediting`
  line `shall be deemed to be the credit of such income to the account of the payee, and the provisions of this`
  line `section shall apply accordingly.]`
  line `3 [194LBC.Income in respect of investment in securitization trust. — ( 1 ) Where any income is`
  line `payable to an investor, being a resident, in respect of an investment in a securitisation trust specified in`
  line `clause ( d ) of the Explanation occurring after section 115TCA, the person responsible for making the`
  line `payment shall, at the time of credit of such income to the account of the payee or at the time of payment`
  line `thereof in cash or by issue of a cheque or draft or by any other mode, whichever is earlier, deduct`
  line `income-tax thereon, at the rate of —`
  line `( i ) twenty-five per cent., if the payee is an individual or a Hindu undivided family;`
  line `( ii ) thirty per cent., if the payee is any other person.`
  line `( 2 ) Where any income is payable to an investor, being a non-resident (not being a company) or a`
  line `foreign company, in respect of an investment in a securitisation trust specified in clause ( d ) of`
  line `the Explanation occurring after section 115TCA, the person responsible for making the payment shall, at`
  line `the time of credit of such income to the account of the payee or at the time of payment thereof in cash or`
  line `by issue of a cheque or draft or by any other mode, whichever is earlier, deduct income-tax thereon, at the`
  line `rates in force.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “investor” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( a ) of the Explanation occurring`
  line `after section 115TCA;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 83, for “deduct income - tax thereon at the rate of ten per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2016).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 84, ibid (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
