obj_root_law_sections_653_content:
  string
  line 653
  line `( b ) where any income as aforesaid is credited to any account, whether called “suspense account”`
  line `or by any other name, in the books of account of the person liable to pay such income, such crediting`
  line `shall be deemed to be the credit of such income to the account of the payee, and the provisions of this`
  line `section shall apply accordingly.]`
  line `1 [194LC. Income by way of interest from Indian company. — ( 1 ) Where any income by way of`
  line `interest referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) is payable to a non-resident, not being a company or to a foreign`
  line `company by a specified company 2 [or a business trust], the person responsible for making the payment,`
  line `shall at the time of credit of such income to the account of the payee or at the time of payment thereof in`
  line `cash or by issue of a cheque or draft or by any other mode, whichever is earlier, deduct the income-tax`
  line `thereon at the rate of five per cent.`
  line `( 2 ) The interest referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be the income by way of interest payable by the`
  line `specified company 2 [or the business trust], —`
  line `3 [( i ) in respect of monies borrowed by it in foreign currency from a source outside India, —`
  line `( a ) under a loan agreement at any time on or after the 1st day of July, 2012 but before the`
  line `4 [1st day of July,2020 ]; or`
  line `( b ) by way of issue of long-term infrastructure bonds at any time on or after the 1st day of`
  line `July, 2012 but before the 1st day of October, 2014; or`
  line `( c ) by way of issue of any long-term bond including long-term infrastructure bond at any`
  line `time on or after the 1st day of October, 2014 but before the 4 [1st day of July, 2020 ],`
  line `as approved by the Central Government in this behalf; 5 [ or ]`
  line `6 [ ( ia ) in respect of monies borrowed by it from a source outside India by way of issue of rupee`
  line `denominated bond before the 1st day of July, 2020, and ]`
  line `( ii ) to the extent to which such interest does not exceed the amount of interest calculated at the`
  line `rate approved by the Central Government in this behalf, having regard to the terms of the loan or the`
  line `bond and its repayment.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purpose of this section —`
  line `( a ) “foreign currency” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( m ) of section 2 of the`
  line `Foreign Exchange Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999);`
  line `( b ) ”specified company” means an Indian company.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 76 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 59 (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 59, ibid., for clause ( i ) (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 68, for “1st day of July, 2017” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2018).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 68, ibid., for “and” (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `6. Ins. by s. 68, ibid (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_653_footnotes:
