  title `Page 654`
  content obj_root_law_sections_654_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_654_footnotes
  sourcePage 654
obj_root_law_sections_654_content:
  string
  line 654
  line `1 [194LD. Income by way of interest on certain bonds and Government securities. — ( 1 ) Any`
  line `person who is responsible for paying to a person being a Foreign Institutional Investor or a Qualified`
  line `Foreign Investor, any income by way of interest referred to in sub-section ( 2 ), shall, at the time of credit`
  line `of such income to the account of the payee or at the time of payment of such income in cash or by the`
  line `issue of a cheque or draft or by any other mode, whichever is earlier, deduct income-tax thereon at the`
  line `rate of five per cent.`
  line `( 2 ) The income by way of interest referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be the interest payable on or`
  line `after the 1st day of June, 2013 but before the 2 [1st day of July, 2020 ] in respect of investment made by the`
  line `payee in —`
  line `( i ) a rupee denominated bond of an Indian company; or`
  line `( ii ) a Government security:`
  line `Provided that the rate of interest in respect of bond referred to in clause ( i ) shall not exceed the rate as`
  line `may be notified by the Central Government in this behalf.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purpose of this section, —`
  line `( a )“Foreign Institutional Investor” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( a ) of`
  line `the Explanation to section 115AD;`
  line `( b )“Government security” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( b ) of section 2 of the`
  line `Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956);`
  line `( c )“Qualified Foreign Investor” shall have the meaning assigned to it in the Circular No.`
  line `Cir/IMD/DF/14/2011, dated the 9th August, 2011, as amended from time to time, issued by the`
  line `Securities and Exchange Board of India, under section 11 of the Securities and Exchange Board of`
  line `India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992).]`
  line `195. Other sums. — 3 [ ( 1 ) Any person responsible for paying to a non-resident, not being a company,`
  line `or to a foreign company, 4 [any interest (not being interest referred to in section 194LB or section`
  line `194LC)] 5 [or section 194LD] 6 *** or any other sum chargeable under the provisions of this Act (not being`
  line `income chargeable under the head “Salaries” 7 ***) shall, at the time of credit of such income to the`
  line `account of the payee or at the time of payment thereof in cash or by the issue of a cheque or draft or by`
  line `any other mode, whichever is earlier, deduct income-tax thereon at the rates in force:`
  line `8 [Provided that in the case of interest payable by the Government or a public sector bank within the`
  line `meaning of clause ( 23D ) of section 10 or a public financial institution within the meaning of that clause,`
  line `deduction of tax shall be made only at the time of payment thereof in cash or by the issue of a cheque or`
  line `draft or by any other mode:]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 69, for “1st day of July, 2017” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2018).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 49, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 77, for “any interest” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2012).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 48 (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
  line `6. The words “(not being interest on securities)” omitted by Act 32 of 2003, s. 80 (w.e.f. 1 -6-2003).`
  line `7. The words “or dividends” omitted by Act 49 of 1991, s. 56 (w.e.f. 1 -10-1991).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 36 of 1989, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_654_footnotes:
  string
