obj_root_law_sections_655:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-655
  sectionNo (655)
  orderNo 655
  title `Page 655`
  content obj_root_law_sections_655_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_655_footnotes
  sourcePage 655
obj_root_law_sections_655_content:
  string
  line 655
  line `1 [Provided further that no such deduction shall be made in respect of any dividends referred to`
  line `in section 115-O.]`
  line `Explanation 2 [ 1 ]. — For the purposes of this section, where any interest or other sum as aforesaid is`
  line `credited to any account, whether called “Interest payable account” or “Suspense account” or by any other`
  line `name, in the books of account of the person liable to pay such income, such crediting shall be deemed to`
  line `be credit of such income to the account of the payee and the provisions of this section shall apply`
  line accordingly.]
  line `3 [ Explanation 2. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that the obligation to comply with`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) and to make deduction thereunder applies and shall be deemed to have always applied and`
  line `extends and shall be deemed to have always extended to all persons, resident or non-resident, whether or`
  line `not the non-resident person has —`
  line `( i ) a residence or place of business or business connection in India; or`
  line `( ii ) any other presence in any manner whatsoever in India.]`
  line `( 2 ) Where the person responsible for paying any such sum chargeable under this Act ( 4 [other than`
  line `salary]) to a non-resident considers that the whole of such sum would not be income chargeable in the`
  line `case of the recipient, he may make an application to the 5 [Assessing Officer] to determine, 6 [by general or`
  line `special order], the appropriate proportion of such sum so chargeable, and upon such determination, tax`
  line `shall be deducted under sub-section ( 1 ) only on that proportion of the sum which is so chargeable.`
  line `7 * * * * *`
  line `8 [( 3 ) Subject to rules made under sub-section ( 5 ), any person entitled to receive any interest or other`
  line `sum on which income-tax has to be deducted under sub-section ( 1 ) may make an application in the`
  line `prescribed form to the 5 [Assessing Officer] for the grant of a certificate authorising him to receive such`
  line `interest or other sum without deduction of tax under that sub-section, and where any such certificate is`
  line `granted, every person responsible for paying such interest or other sum to the person to whom such`
  line `certificate is granted shall, so long as the certificate is in force, make payment of such interest or other`
  line `sum without deducting tax thereon under sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 4 ) A certificate granted under sub-section ( 3 ) shall remain in force till the expiry of the period`
  line `specified therein or, if it is cancelled by the 5 [Assessing Officer] before the expiry of such period, till such`
  line cancellation.
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 80 (w.e.f. 1-4-2003). Earlier the proviso was omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 80 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002)`
  line `which was inserted by Act 26 of 1997, s. 49 (w.e.f. 1-6-1997).`
  line `2. The Explanation renumbered as Explanation 1 thereof by Act 23 of 2012, s. 77 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 77, ibid. (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 80, for “other than interest on securities and salary” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2003). Earlier the words`
  line `“other than interest including interest on securities” substituted by Act 66 of 1976, s. 22, for “other than interest on`
  line `securities” (w.e.f. 1 -6- 1976) and the word “dividend” w as omitted by Act 49 of 1991, s. 56 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 39, for “in the prescribed manner (w.r.e.f. 1 -3-1988). Earlier the quoted words were`
  line `substit uted by Act 11 of 1987, s. 49 for “by general or special order” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1987).`
  line `7. The proviso omitted by Act 49 of 1991, s. 56 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991). Earlier the proviso was inserted by Act 11 of 1987, s. 49`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 19 of 1970, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-1970).`
