obj_root_law_sections_656_content:
  string
  line 656
  line `( 5 ) The Board may, having regard to the convenience of assessees and the interests of revenue, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules specifying the cases in which, and the circumstances under`
  line `which, an application may be made for the grant of a certificate under sub-section ( 3 ) and the conditions`
  line `subject to which such certificate may be granted and providing for all other matters connected therewith.]`
  line `1 [( 6 ) The person responsible for paying to a non-resident, not being a company, or to a foreign`
  line `company, any sum, whether or not chargeable under the provisions of this Act, shall furnish the`
  line `information relating to payment of such sum, in such form and manner, as may be prescribed.]`
  line `2 [( 7 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ) and sub-section ( 2 ), the Board may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify a class of persons or cases, where the person responsible for`
  line `paying to a non-resident, not being a company, or to a foreign company, any sum, whether or not`
  line `chargeable under the provisions of this Act, shall make an application to the Assessing Officer to`
  line `determine, by general or special order, the appropriate proportion of sum chargeable, and upon such`
  line `determination, tax shall be deducted under sub-section ( 1 ) on that proportion of the sum which is so`
  line chargeable.]
  line `3 [ 195A. Income payable “net of tax”. — 4 [In a case other than that referred to in sub-section ( 1A )`
  line `of section 192, where under an agreement] or other arrangement, the tax chargeable on any income`
  line `referred to in the foregoing provisions of this Chapter is to be borne by the person by whom the income is`
  line `payable, then, for the purposes of deduction of tax under those provisions such income shall be increased`
  line `to such amount as would, after deduction of tax thereon at the rates in force for the financial year in which`
  line `such income is payable, be equal to the net amount payable under such agreement or arrangement.]`
  line `5 [ 196. Interest or dividend or other sums payable to Government, Reserve Bank or certain`
  line `corporations. — Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this Chapter, no`
  line `deduction of tax shall be made by any person from any sums payable to —`
  line `( i ) the Government, or`
  line `( ii ) the Reserve Bank of India, or`
  line `( iii ) a corporation established by or under a Central Act which is, under any law for the time`
  line `being in force, exempt from income-tax on its income, or`
  line `( iv ) a Mutual Fund specified under clause ( 23D ) of section 10,`
  line `where such sum is payable to it by way of interest or dividend in respect of any securities or shares owned`
  line `by it or in which it has full beneficial interest, or any other income accruing or arising to it.]`
  line `6 [ 196A. Income in respect of units of non-residents. — ( 1 ) Any person responsible for paying to a`
  line `non-resident, not being a company, or to a foreign company, any income in respect of units of a Mutual`
  line `Fund specified under clause ( 23D ) of section 10 or of the Unit Trust of India shall, at the time of credit of`
  line `such income to the account of the payee or at the time of payment thereof in cash or by the issue of a`
  line `cheque or draft or by any other mode, whichever is earlier, deduct income-tax thereon at the rate of`
  line `twenty per cent:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 49, for sub-section ( 6 ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2015). Earlier sub-section ( 6 ) was inserted by`
  line `Act 18 of 2008, s. 44 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 77 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 81, for “Where, under an agreement” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2002).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 75, for section 196 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988). Earlier section 196 was substituted by Act 20 of 1967, s.`
  line `30 (w.e.f. 1-4-1967).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 37, for section 196A (w.e.f. 1-7-1995).`
