  line 660
  line `1 [( 1D ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, no deduction of tax shall be made by the`
  line `Offshore Banking Unit from the interest paid —`
  line `( a ) on deposit made on or after the 1st day of April, 2005, by a non-resident or a person not`
  line `ordinarily resident in India; or`
  line `( b ) on borrowing, on or after the 1st day of April, 2005, from a non-resident or a person not`
  line `ordinarily resident in India.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- section “Offshore Banking Unit” shall have the same`
  line `meaning as assigned to it in clause ( u ) of section 2 of the Special Economic Zones Act, 2005.]`
  line `2 [( 1E ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Chapter, no deduction of tax shall be made from`
  line `any payment to any person for, or on behalf of, the New Pension System Trust referred to in clause ( 44 )`
  line `of section 10.]`
  line `3 [( 1F ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Chapter, no deduction of tax shall be made from`
  line `such specified payment to such institution, association or body or class of institutions, associations or`
  line `bodies as may be notified by the Central Government in the Official Gazette, in this behalf.]`
  line `( 2 ) The person responsible for paying any income of the nature referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) 4 [or`
  line `sub-section ( 1A )] 5 [or sub-section ( 1C )] shall deliver or cause to be delivered to the 6 [ 7 [Principal Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 8 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] one copy of the`
  line `declaration referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) 4 [or sub-section ( 1A )] 5 [or sub-section ( 1C )] on or before the`
  line `seventh day of the month next following the month in which the declaration is furnished to him.]`
  line `198. Tax deductedis income received. — All sums deducted in accordance with 9 [the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Chapter] shall, for the purpose of computing the income of an assessee, be deemed to`
  line `be income received:`
  line `10 [ Provided that the sum being the tax paid, under sub-section ( 1A ) of section 192 for the purpose of`
  line `computing the income of an assessee, shall not be deemed to be income received.]`
  line `11 [ 199. Credit for tax deducted. — ( 1 ) Any deduction made in accordance with the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Chapter and paid to the Central Government shall be treated as a payment of tax on`
  line `behalf of the person from whose income the deduction was made, or of the owner of the security, or of`
  line `the depositor or of the owner of property or of the unit-holder, or of the shareholder, as the case may be.`
  line `( 2 ) Any sum referred to in sub-section ( 1A ) of section 192 and paid to the Central Government shall`
  line `be treated as the tax paid on behalf of the person in respect of whose income such payment of tax has`
  line `been made.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2005, s. 27 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 10-2-2006).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 63 (w.e.f. 1-4-2009).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 78 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 77 (w.e.f. 1-6-1992).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 85 (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 40, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-10-2004).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 86 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 45, for section 199 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
