obj_root_law_sections_661_content:
  string
  line 661
  line `( 3 ) The Board may, for the purposes of giving credit in respect of tax deducted or tax paid in terms of`
  line `the provisions of this Chapter, make such rules as may be necessary, including the rules for the purposes`
  line `of giving credit to a person other than those referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) and sub-section ( 2 ) and also the`
  line `assessment year for which such credit may be given.]`
  line `200. Duty of person deducting tax. — 1 [( 1 )] Any person deducting any sum in accordance with 2 [the`
  line `foregoing provisions of this Chapter] shall pay within the prescribed time, the sum so deducted to the`
  line `credit of the Central Government or as the Board directs.`
  line `3 [( 2 ) Any person being an employer, referred to in sub-section ( 1A ) of section 192 shall pay, within`
  line `the prescribed time, the tax to the credit of the Central Government or as the Board directs.]`
  line `4 [( 2A ) In case of an office of the Government, where the sum deducted in accordance with the`
  line `foregoing provisions of this Chapter or tax referred to in sub-section ( 1A ) of section 192 has been paid to`
  line `the credit of the Central Government without the production of a challan, the Pay and Accounts Officer or`
  line `the Treasury Officer or the Cheque Drawing and Disbursing Officer or any other person, by whatever`
  line `name called, who is responsible for crediting such sum or tax to the credit of the Central Government,`
  line `shall deliver or cause to be delivered to the prescribed income-tax authority, or to the person authorised`
  line `by such authority, a statement in such form, verified in such manner, setting forth such particulars and`
  line `within such time as may be prescribed.]`
  line `5 [( 3 ) Any person deducting any sum on or after the 1st day of April, 2005 in accordance with the`
  line `foregoing provisions of this Chapter or, as the case may be, any person being an employer referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 1A ) of section 192 shall, after paying the tax deducted to the credit of the Central`
  line `Government within the prescribed time, prepare such statements for such period as may be prescribed and`
  line `deliver or cause to be delivered to the prescribed income-tax authority or the person authorised by such`
  line `authority such statement in such form and verified in such manner and setting forth such particulars and`
  line `within such time as may be prescribed:]`
  line `6 [Provided that the person may also deliver to the prescribed authority a correction statement for`
  line `rectification of any mistake or to add, delete or update the information furnished in the statement`
  line `delivered under this sub-section in such form and verified in such manner as may be specified by the`
  line authority.]
  line `7 [ 200A. Processing of statements of tax deducted at source. — ( 1 ) Where a statement of tax`
  line `deduction at source 8 [or a correction statement] has been made by a person deducting any sum (hereafter`
  line `referred to in this section as deductor) under section 200, such statement shall be processed in the`
  line `following manner, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the sums deductible under this Chapter shall be computed after making the following`
  line `adjustments, namely: —`
  line `( i ) any arithmetical error in the statement; or`
  line `1. Section 200 re-numbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 20 of 2002, s. 88 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 42, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-10-2004).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 88 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 51 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 60 (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 61 (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
