obj_root_law_sections_662_content:
  string
  line 662
  line `( ii ) an incorrect claim, apparent from any information in the statement;`
  line `( b ) the interest, if any, shall be computed on the basis of the sums deductible as computed in the`
  line statement;
  line `1 [( c ) the fee, if any, shall be computed in accordance with the provisions of section 234E;`
  line `( d ) the sum payable by, or the amount of refund due to, the deductor shall be determined after`
  line `adjustment of the amount computed under clause ( b ) and clause ( c ) against any amount paid`
  line `under section 200 or section 201 orsection 234E and any amount paid otherwise by way of tax or`
  line `interest or fee;`
  line `( e ) an intimation shall be prepared or generated and sent to the deductor specifying the sum`
  line `determined to be payable by, or the amount of refund due to, him under clause ( d ); and`
  line `( f ) the amount of refund due to the deductor in pursuance of the determination under clause ( d )`
  line `shall be granted to the deductor:]`
  line `Provided that no intimation under this sub-section shall be sent after the expiry of one year from`
  line `the end of the financial year in which the statement is filed.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- section, “an incorrect claim apparent from any`
  line `information in the statement” shall mean a claim, on the basis of an entry, in the statement—`
  line `( i ) of an item, which is inconsistent with another entry of the same or some other item in such`
  line statement;
  line `( ii ) in respect of rate of deduction of tax at source, where such rate is not in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) For the purposes of processing of statements under sub-section ( 1 ), the Board may make a scheme`
  line `for centralised processing of statements of tax deducted at source to expeditiously determine the tax`
  line `payable by, or the refund due to, the deductor as required under the said sub-section.]`
  line `201. Consequences of failure to deduct or pay. — 2 [( 1 ) Where any person, including the principal`
  line `officer of a company, —`
  line `( a ) who is required to deduct any sum in accordance with the provisions of this Act; or`
  line `( b ) referred to in sub-section ( 1A ) of section 192, being an employer,`
  line `does not deduct, or does not pay, or after so deducting fails to pay, the whole or any part of the tax, as`
  line `required by or under this Act, then, such person, shall, without prejudice to any other consequences which`
  line `he may incur, be deemed to be an assessee in default in respect of such tax:`
  line `3 [Provided that any person, including the principal officer of a company, who fails to deduct the`
  line `whole or any part of the tax in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter on the sum paid to a`
  line `resident or on the sum credited to the account of a resident shall not be deemed to be an assessee in`
  line `default in respect of such tax if such resident —`
  line `( i ) has furnished his return of income under section 139;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 52, for clauses ( c ) to ( e ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 46, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.r.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 79 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
