  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_663_footnotes
  sourcePage 663
obj_root_law_sections_663_content:
  string
  line 663
  line `( ii ) has taken into account such sum for computing income in such return of income; and`
  line `( iii ) has paid the tax due on the income declared by him in such return of income,`
  line `and the person furnishes a certificate to this effect from an accountant in such form as may be prescribed:]`
  line `1 [Provided further that] no penalty shall be charged under section 221 from such person, unless the`
  line `Assessing Officer is satisfied that such person, without good and sufficient reasons, has failed to deduct`
  line `and pay such tax.]`
  line `2 [( 1A ) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ), if any such person, principal officer or`
  line `company as is referred to in that sub-section does not deduct the whole or any part of the tax or after`
  line `deducting fails to pay the tax as required by or under this Act, he or it shall be liable to pay simple`
  line `interest, —`
  line `( i ) at one per cent for every month or part of a month on the amount of such tax from the date on`
  line `which such tax was deductible to the date on which such tax is deducted; and`
  line `( ii ) at one and one-half per cent for every month or part of a month on the amount of such tax`
  line `from the date on which such tax was deducted to the date on which such tax is actually paid,`
  line `and such interest shall be paid before furnishing the statement in accordance with the provisions of sub-`
  line `section (3) of section 200:]`
  line `1 [Provided that in case any person, including the principal officer of a company fails to deduct the`
  line `whole or any part of the tax in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter on the sum paid to a`
  line `resident or on the sum credited to the account of a resident but is not deemed to be an assessee in default`
  line `under the first proviso to sub-section ( 1 ), the interest under clause ( i ) shall be payable from the date on`
  line `which such tax was deductible to the date of furnishing of return of income by such resident.]`
  line `( 2 ) Where the tax has not been paid as aforesaid after it is deducted, 3 [the amount of the tax together`
  line `with the amount of simple interest thereon referred to in sub-section ( 1A ) shall be a charge] upon all the`
  line `assets of the person, or the company, as the case may be, referred to in sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `4 [ 5 [( 3 ) No order shall be made under sub-section ( 1 ) deeming a person to be an assessee in default for`
  line `failure to deduct the whole or any part of the tax from a person resident in India, at any time after the`
  line `expiry of seven years from the end of the financial year in which payment is made or credit is given.]`
  line `( 4 ) The provisions of sub-clause ( ii ) of sub-section (3) of section 153 and of Explanation 1 to section`
  line `153 shall, so far as may, apply to the time limit prescribed in sub-section ( 3 ).]`
  line `6 [ Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, the expression “accountant” shall have the meaning`
  line `assigned to it in the Explanation to sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288.]`
  line `202. Deduction only one mode of recovery. — The power to 7 [recover tax] by deduction under 8 [the`
  line `foregoing provisions of this Chapter] shall be without prejudice to any other mode of recovery.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 79, for “Provided that” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012)`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 42, for sub-section ( 1A ) (w.e.f. 1-7-2010).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 13 of 1966, s. 26, for “it shall be a charge” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1966).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 66 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 62, for sub-section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 1-10-2014). Earlier sub-section ( 3 ) was amended by Act 23 of`
  line `2012, s. 79 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 79 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 53 for “levy tax” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1987).`
  line `8. Subs by Act 23 of 2004, s. 43, for certain words, figures and letters the portion beginning with the words “the provisions`
  line `of section 192” and ending with the words “section 196D” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2004).`
