obj_root_law_sections_664_content:
  string
  line 664
  line `1 [ 203. Certificate for tax deducted. — 2 [( 1 )] Every person deducting tax in accordance with 3 [the`
  line `foregoing provisions of this Chapter] 4 [shall, within such period as may be prescribed from the time of`
  line `credit or payment of the sum, or, as the case may be, from the time of issue of a cheque or warrant for`
  line `payment of any dividend to a shareholder], furnish to the person to whose account such credit is given or`
  line `to whom such payment is made or the cheque or warrant is issued, a certificate to the effect that tax has`
  line `been deducted, and specifying the amount so deducted, the rate at which the tax has been deducted and`
  line `such other particulars as may be prescribed.]`
  line `5 [( 2 ) Every person, being an employer, referred to in sub-section ( 1A ) of section 192 shall, within`
  line `such period, as may be prescribed, furnish to the person in respect of whose income such payment of tax`
  line `has been made, a certificate to the effect that tax has been paid to the Central Government, and specify the`
  line `amount so paid, the rate at which the tax has been paid and such other particulars as may be prescribed.]`
  line `6 * * * * *`
  line `7 [ 203A. Tax deduction and collection account number. — ( 1 ) Every person, deducting tax or`
  line `collecting tax in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter, who has not been allotted a tax deduction`
  line `account number or, as the case may be, a tax collection account number, shall, within such time as may be`
  line `prescribed, apply to the Assessing Officer for the allotment of a “tax deduction and collection account`
  line number”.
  line `( 2 ) Where a “tax deduction account number” or, as the case may be, a “tax collection account`
  line `number” or a “tax deduction and collection account number” has been allotted to a person, such person`
  line `shall quote such number —`
  line `( a ) in all challans for the payment of any sum in accordance with the provisions of section 200 or`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ) of section 206C;`
  line `( b ) in all certificates furnished under section 203 or sub-section ( 5 ) of section 206C;`
  line `8 [( ba ) in all the 9 *** statements prepared and delivered or caused to be delivered in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of sub-section ( 3 ) of section 200 or sub-section ( 3 ) of section 206C;]`
  line `( c ) in all the returns, delivered in accordance with the provisions of section 206 or sub-section`
  line `( 5A ) or sub-section ( 5B ) of section 206C to any income-tax authority; and`
  line `( d ) in all other documents pertaining to such transactions as may be prescribed in the interests of`
  line revenue.]
  line `10 [( 3 ) The provisions of this section shall not apply to such person, as may be notified by the Central`
  line `Government in this behalf.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 30, for section 203, (w.e.f. 1-4-1967).`
  line `2. Section 203 renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 20 of 2002, s. 90 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 44, for the portion beginning with the words “the provisions of section 192” and ending with`
  line `the words “section 196D” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2004).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 54, for “shall, at the time of credit of payment of the sum, or, as the case may be, at the ti me`
  line `of issue of a cheque or warrant for payment of any dividend to a shareholder” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1987).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 90 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `6. Sub-section ( 3 ) omitted by Act 14 of 2010, s. 43 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 45, for section 203A (w.e.f. 1-10-2004).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 44 (w.e.f. 1-6-2006).`
  line `9. The word “quarterly” omitted by Act 33 of 2009, s. 67 (w.e.f. 1 -10-2009).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 53 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
