  content obj_root_law_sections_666_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_666_footnotes
  sourcePage 666
obj_root_law_sections_666_content:
  string
  line 666
  line `205. Bar against direct demand on assessee. — Where tax is deductible at the source under 1 [the`
  line `foregoing provisions of this Chapter], the assessee shall not be called upon to pay the tax himself to the`
  line `extent to which tax has been deducted from that income.`
  line `2 [ 206. Persons deducting tax to furnish prescribed returns. — 3 [( 1 )] The prescribed personin the`
  line `case of every office of Government, the principal officer in the case of every company, the prescribed`
  line `personin the case of every local authority or other public body or association, every private employer and`
  line `every other person 4 [responsible for deducting tax before the 1st day of April, 2005] under the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Chapter 5 [shall, within the prescribed time after the end of each financial year, prepare`
  line `and deliver or cause to be delivered] to the 6 [prescribed income-tax authorityor such other authority or`
  line `agency as may be prescribed], such returns in such form and verified in such manner and setting forth`
  line `such particulars as may be prescribed:]`
  line `7 [Provided that the Board may, if it considers necessary or expedient so to do, frame a scheme for the`
  line `purposes of filing such returns with such other authority or agency referred to in this sub-section.]`
  line `8 [( 2 ) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ), the person responsible for deducting tax`
  line `under the foregoing provisions of this Chapter 9 [other than the prescribed person in the case of every`
  line `office of the Government andthe principal officer in the case of every company] may, at his option,`
  line `deliver or cause to be delivered such return to the prescribed income-tax authority in accordance with`
  line `such scheme as may be specified by the Board in this behalf, by notification in the Official Gazette, and`
  line `subject to such conditions as may be specified therein, on or before the prescribed time after the end of`
  line `each financial year, on a floppy, diskette, magnetic cartridge tape, CD-ROM or any other computer`
  line `readable media (hereinafter referred to as the computer media) and in the manner as may be specified in`
  line `that scheme:`
  line `10 [Provided that the prescribed person in the case of every office of Government and the principal`
  line `officer in the case of every company responsible for deducting tax under the foregoing provisions of this`
  line `Chapter shall, deliver or cause to be delivered, within the prescribed time after the end of each financial`
  line `year, such returns on computer media under the said scheme.]`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, a return filed on`
  line `computer media shall be deemed to be a return for the purposes of this section and the rules made`
  line `thereunder and shall be admissible in any proceedings thereunder, without further proof of production of`
  line `the original, as evidence of any contents of the original or of any fact stated therein.`
  line `( 4 ) Where the Assessing Officer considers that the return delivered or caused to be delivered under`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) is defective, he may intimate the defect to the person responsible for deducting tax or the`
  line `principal officer in the case of a company, as the case may be, and give him an opportunity of rectifying`
  line `the defect within a period of fifteen days from the date of such intimation or within such further period`
  line `which, on an application made in this behalf, the Assessing Officer may, in his discretion, allow; and if`
  line `the defect is not rectified within the said period of fifteen days or, as the case may be, the further period`
  line `so allowed, then, notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, such return shall`
  line `be treated as an invalid return and the provisions of this Act shall apply as if such person had failed to`
  line `deliver the return.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 48, for certain words, figures and letter (w.e.f. 1-10-2004).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 56, for section 206 (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `3. Section 206 renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) by Act 26 of 1997, s. 52 (w.e.f. 1-4-1997).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 46, for “responsible for deducting tax” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 62, for “shall prepare, within the prescribed time after the end of each financial year, and`
  line `deliver or cause to be delivered ” (w.e.f. 27 -9-1991).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 49, for “prescribed income - tax authority” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2004).`
  line `7. Ins. by s. 49, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-2004).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 86, for sub-sections ( 2 ) and ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line `9. Subs. by Ac t 23 of 2004, s. 49, for “other than the principal officer in the case of every company” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2005).`
  line `10. Subs. by s. 49, ibid., for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
