obj_root_law_sections_667_content:
  string
  line 667
  line `1 [ 206A. Furnishing of quarterlyreturn in respect of payment of interest to residents without`
  line `deduction of tax. — ( 1 ) Any banking company or co-operative society or public company referred to in`
  line `the proviso to clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 3 ) of section 194A responsible for paying to a resident any`
  line `income 2 [not exceeding ten thousand rupees, where the payer is a banking company or a co-operative`
  line `society, and five thousand rupees in any other case] by way of interest (other than interest on securities),`
  line `shall prepare 3 [such statements for such period as may be prescribed] and deliver or cause to be delivered`
  line `to the prescribed income-tax authorityor the person authorised by such authority the quarterly returns as`
  line `aforesaid, in the prescribed form, verified in such manner and within such time as may be prescribed, on a`
  line `floppy, diskette, magnetic cartridge tape, CD-ROM or any other computer readable media.`
  line `( 2 ) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, require any person other`
  line `than a person mentioned in sub-section ( 1 ) responsible for paying to a resident any income liable for`
  line `deduction of tax at source under Chapter XVII, to prepare and deliver or cause to be delivered 4 [such`
  line `statements] in the prescribed form and verified in such manner and within such time as may be`
  line `prescribed, to the prescribed income-tax authority or the person authorised by such authority on a floppy,`
  line `diskette, magnetic cartridge tape, CD-ROM or any other computer readable media.]`
  line `5 [ 206AA. Requirement to furnish Permanent Account Number. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other provisions of this Act, any person entitled to receive any sum or income or`
  line `amount, on which tax is deductible under Chapter XVIIB (hereafter referred to as deductee) shall furnish`
  line `his Permanent Account Number to the person responsible for deducting such tax (hereafter referred to as`
  line `deductor), failing which tax shall be deducted at the higher of the following rates, namely: —`
  line `( i ) at the rate specified in the relevant provision of this Act; or`
  line `( ii ) at the rate or rates in force; or`
  line `( iii ) at the rate of twenty per cent.`
  line `( 2 ) No declaration under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 1A ) or sub-section ( 1C ) of section 197A shall`
  line `be valid unless the person furnishes his Permanent Account Number in such declaration.`
  line `( 3 ) In case any declaration becomes invalid under sub-section ( 2 ), the deductor shall deduct the tax at`
  line `source in accordance with the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 4 ) No certificate under section 197 shall be granted unless the application made under that section`
  line `contains the Permanent Account Number of the applicant.`
  line `( 5 ) The deductee shall furnish his Permanent Account Number to the deductor and both shall indicate`
  line `the same in all the correspondence, bills, vouchers and other documents which are sent to each other.`
  line `( 6 ) Where the Permanent Account Number provided to the deductor is invalid or does not belong to`
  line `the deductee, it shall be deemed that the deductee has not furnished his Permanent Account Number to`
  line `the deductor and the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) shall apply accordingly. ]`
  line `6 [( 7 ) The provisions of this section shall not apply to a non-resident, not being a company, or to a`
  line `foreign company, in respect of —`
  line `( i ) payment of interest on long-term bonds as referred to in section 194LC; and`
  line `( ii ) any other payment subject to such conditions as may be prescribed.]`
  line `206B. [Person paying dividend to certain residents without deduction of tax to furnish`
  line `prescribed return]. — Omitted by the Finance ( No. 2 ) Act, 1996(33 of 1996), s. 51( w.e.f. 1-10-1996).`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 52 (w.e.f. 1-6-2005).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 60, for “not exceeding five thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2007).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 68, for “quarterly returns for the period ending on the 30th June, the 30th September, the 31s t`
  line `December and the 31st March in each financial year” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2009).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 68, ibid., for “quarterly returns” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2009).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 69, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 87, for sub-section ( 7 ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
