obj_root_law_sections_668_content:
  string
  line 668
  line `1 [ BB. — Collection at source`
  line `206C. Profits and gains from the business of trading in alcoholic liquor, forest produce, scrap,`
  line `etc. — 2 [( 1 ) Every person, being a seller shall, at the time of debiting of the amount payable by the buyer`
  line `to the account of the buyer or at the time of receipt of such amount from the said buyer in cash or by the`
  line `issue of a cheque or draft or by any other mode, whichever is earlier, collect from the buyer of any goods`
  line `of the nature specified in column (2) of the Table below, a sum equal to the percentage, specified in the`
  line `corresponding entry in column (3) of the said Table, of such amount as income-tax:`
  line `3 [TABLE`
  line `Sl. No. Nat ure of goods Percentage`
  line `( 1 ) ( 2 ) ( 3 )`
  line `( i ) Alcoholic Liquor for human consumption One per cent`
  line `( ii ) Tendu leaves Five per cent`
  line `( iii ) Timber obtained under a forest lease Two and one - half per cent`
  line `( iv ) Timber obtained by any mode other than under a forest`
  line lease
  line `Two and one - half per cent`
  line `( v ) Any other forest produce not being timber or tendu leaves Two and one - half per cent`
  line `( vi ) Scrap One per cent]`
  line `4 [( vii ) Minerals, being coal or lignite or iron ore One per cent:]`
  line `5 [Provided that every person, being a seller shall at the time, during the period beginning on the 1st`
  line `day of June, 2003 and ending on the day immediately preceding the date on which the Taxation Laws`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2003 comes into force, of debiting of the amount payable by the buyer to the account`
  line `of the buyer or of receipt of such amount from the said buyer in cash or by the issue of a cheque or draft`
  line `or by any other mode, whichever is earlier, collect from the buyer of any goods of the nature specified in`
  line `column ( 2 ) of the Table as it stood immediately before the 1st day of June, 2003, a sum equal to the`
  line `percentage, specified in the corresponding entry in column ( 3 ) of the said Table, of such amount as`
  line `income-tax in accordance with the provisions of this section as they stood immediately before the 1st day`
  line `of June, 2003.]]`
  line `6 [( 1A ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), no collection of tax shall be made in`
  line `the case of a buyer, who is resident in India, if such buyer furnishes to the person responsible for`
  line `collecting tax, a declaration in writing in duplicate in the prescribed form and verified in the prescribed`
  line `manner to the effect that the goods referred to in column (2) of the aforesaid Table are to be utilised for`
  line `the purposes of manufacturing, processing or producing articles or things 4 [or for the purposes of`
  line `generation of power] and not for trading purposes.`
  line `1. Ins. by 26 of 1988, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-6-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 79, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1992). Earlier sub-section ( 1 ) amended by Act 3 of 1989, s.`
  line `34 (w.r.e.f. 1-6-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 9, for the Table (w.e.f. 8-9-2003). Earlier substitution by 18 of 1992, s. 75 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992),`
  line `as so amended by Act 32 of 2003, s. 86 (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 81 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 9, for the proviso (w.e.f. 8-9-2003).`
  line `6. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-9-2003).`
