obj_root_law_sections_669_content:
  string
  line 669
  line `( 1B ) The person responsible for collecting tax under this section shall deliver or cause to be delivered`
  line `to the 1 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 2 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner] one copy of the declaration referred to in sub-section ( 1A ) on or before the seventh day of`
  line `the month next following the month in which the declaration is furnished to him.]`
  line `3 [( 1C ) Every person, who grants a lease or a licence or enters into a contract or otherwise transfers`
  line `any right or interest either in whole or in part in any parking lot or toll plaza or mine or quarry, to another`
  line `person, other than a public sector company (hereafter in this section referred to as “licensee or lessee”) for`
  line `the use of such parking lot or toll plaza or mine or quarry for the purpose of business shall, at the time of`
  line `debiting of the amount payable by the licensee or lessee to the account of thelicensee or lessee or at the`
  line `time of receipt of such amount from the licensee or lessee in cash or by the issue of a cheque or draft or`
  line `by any other mode, whichever is earlier, collect from the licensee or lessee of any such licence, contract`
  line `or lease of the nature specified in column ( 2 ) of the Table below, a sum equal to the percentage, specified`
  line `in the corresponding entry in column ( 3 ) of the said Table, of such amount as income-tax:`
  line TABLE
  line `Sl. No. Nature of contract or licence or lease, etc. Percentage`
  line `( 1 ) ( 2 ) ( 3 )`
  line `( i ) Parking lot Two per cent.`
  line `( ii ) Toll plaza Two per cent.`
  line `( iii ) Mining and quarrying Two per cent.]`
  line `4 [ Explanation 1. — For the purposes of this sub- section, “mining and quarrying” shall not include`
  line `mining and quarrying of mineral oil.`
  line `Explanation 2. — For the purposes of Explanation 1, “mineral oil” includes petroleum and natural`
  line gas.]
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `( 1F )Every person, being a seller, who receives any amount as consideration for sale of a motor`
  line `vehicle of the value exceeding ten lakh rupees, shall, at the time of receipt of such amount, collect from`
  line `the buyer, a sum equal to one per cent of the sale consideration as income-tax. ]`
  line `( 2 ) The power to recover tax by collection under sub-section ( 1 ) 3 [or sub-section ( 1C )] 6 ***shall be`
  line `without prejudice to any other mode of recovery.`
  line `( 3 ) Any person collecting any amount under sub-section ( 1 ) 3 [or sub-section ( 1C ) 6 ***shall pay`
  line `within 7 [the prescribed time] the amount so collected to the credit of the Central Government or as the`
  line `Board directs:`
  line `8 [Provided that the person collecting tax on or after the 1st day of April, 2005 in accordance with the`
  line `foregoing provisions of this section shall, after paying the tax collected to the credit of the Central`
  line `Government within the prescribed time, 9 [prepare such statements for such period as may be prescribed]`
  line `and deliver or cause to be delivered to the prescribed income-tax authority, or the person authorised by`
  line `such authority, such statement in such form and verified in such manner and setting forth such particulars`
  line `and within such time as may be prescribed.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2 014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-10-2004).`
  line `4. The Explanations ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 61 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `5. Sub-sections ( 1D ) and ( 1E ) omitted by Act 7 of 2017, s. 72 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `6. The words “or sub -section ( 1D )” omitted by s. 72, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 9, for “seven days” (w.e.f. 8 -9-2003).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 23 of 2003, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-4-2005 ).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 70, for “prepare quarterly statements for the period ending on the 30 th June, the`
  line `30 th September, the 31 st December and the 31 st March in each financial year” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2009).`
