obj_root_law_sections_671_content:
  string
  line 671
  line `1 [Provided that the Board may, if it considers necessary or expedient so to do, frame a scheme for the`
  line `purposes of filing such returns with such other authority or agency referred to in this sub-section.]`
  line `2 [( 5B ) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section ( 5A ), any person collecting tax, other than in`
  line `a case where the seller is a company, the Central Government or a State Government, may at his option,`
  line `deliver or cause to be delivered such return to the prescribed income-tax authority in accordance with`
  line `such scheme as may be specified by the Board in this behalf, by notification in the Official Gazette, and`
  line `subject to such conditions as may be specified therein, on or before the prescribed time after the end of`
  line `each financial year, on a floppy, diskette, magnetic cartridge tape, CD-ROM or any other computer`
  line `readable media (hereinafter referred to as the computer media) and in the manner as may be specified in`
  line `that scheme:`
  line `Provided that where the person collecting tax is a company or the Central Government or a State`
  line `Government, such person shall, in accordance with the provisions of this section, deliver or cause to be`
  line `delivered, within the prescribed time after the end of each financial year, such returns on computer media`
  line `under the said scheme.`
  line `( 5C ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, a return filed`
  line `on computer media shall be deemed to be a return for the purposes of sub-section ( 5A ) and the rules made`
  line `thereunder and shall be admissible in any proceedings made thereunder, without further proof of`
  line `production of the original, as evidence of any contents of the original or of any facts stated therein.`
  line `( 5D )Where the Assessing Officer considers that the return delivered or caused to be delivered under`
  line `sub-section ( 5B ) is defective, he may intimate the defect to the person collecting tax and give him an`
  line `opportunity of rectifying the defect within a period of fifteen days from the date of such intimation or`
  line `within such further period which, on an application made in this behalf, the Assessing Officer may, in his`
  line `discretion, allow; and if the defect is not rectified within the said period of fifteen days or, as the case may`
  line `be, the further period so allowed, then, notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this`
  line `Act, such return shall be treated as an invalid return and the provisions of this Act shall apply as if such`
  line `person had failed to deliver the return.]`
  line `( 6 ) Any person responsible for collecting the tax who fails to collect the tax in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this section, shall, notwithstanding such failure, be liable to pay the tax to the credit of the`
  line `Central Government in accordance with the provisions of sub-section ( 3 ).`
  line `3 [( 6A ) If any person responsible for collecting tax in accordance with the provisions of this section`
  line `does not collect the whole or any part of the tax or after collecting, fails to pay the tax as required by or`
  line `under this Act, he shall, without prejudice to any other consequences which he may incur, be deemed to`
  line `be an assessee in default in respect of the tax:`
  line `4 [Provided that any person 5 ***responsible for collecting tax in accordance with the provisions of this`
  line `section, who fails to collect the whole or any part of the tax on the amount received from a buyer or`
  line `licensee or lessee or on the amount debited to the account of the buyer or licensee or lessee shall not be`
  line `deemed to be an assessee in default in respect of such tax if such buyer or licensee or lessee —`
  line `( i ) has furnished his return of income under section 139;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-10-2004).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 50, ibid., for sub-sections ( 5B ) and ( 5C ) (w.e.f.. 1-4-2005).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 81 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `5. The words “, other than a person referred to in sub -section ( 1D ),” omitted by Act 7 of 2017, s. 72 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
