obj_root_law_sections_672_content:
  string
  line 672
  line `( ii ) has taken into account such amount for computing income in such return of income; and`
  line `( iii ) has paid the tax due on the income declared by him in such return of income,`
  line `and the person furnishes a certificate to this effect from an accountant in such form as may be prescribed:]`
  line `1 [Provided further that] no penalty shall be charged under section 221 from such person unless the`
  line `Assessing Officer is satisfied that the person has without good and sufficient reasons failed to collect and`
  line `pay the tax.]`
  line `( 7 ) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section ( 6 ), if the 2 [person responsible for collecting`
  line `tax] does not collect the tax or after collecting the tax fails to pay it as required under this section, he shall`
  line `be liable to pay simple interest at the rate of 3 [one per cent.] per month or part thereof on the amount of`
  line `such tax from the date on which such tax was collectible to the date on which the tax was actually paid`
  line `4 [and such interest shall be paid before furnishing the quarterly statement for each quarter in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of sub-section ( 3 )]:`
  line `5 [Provided that in case any person 6 ***responsible for collecting tax in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of this section, fails to collect the whole or any part of the tax on the amount received from a buyer or`
  line `licensee or lessee or on the amount debited to the account of the buyer or licensee or lessee but is not`
  line `deemed to be an assessee in default under the first proviso of sub-section ( 6A ), the interest shall be`
  line `payable from the date on which such tax was collectible to the date of furnishing of return of income by`
  line `such buyer or licensee or lessee.]`
  line `( 8 ) Where the tax has not been paid as aforesaid, after it is collected, the amount of the tax together`
  line `with the amount of simple interest thereon referred to in sub-section ( 7 ) shall be a charge upon all the`
  line `assets of the 2 [person responsible for collecting tax].]`
  line `7 [( 9 ) Where the Assessing Officer is satisfied that the total income of the 8 [buyer or licensee or lessee]`
  line `justifies the collection of the tax at any lower rate than the relevant rate specified in sub-section ( 1 ) 9 [or`
  line `sub-section ( 1C )] 10 ***, the Assessing Officer shall, on an application made by the buyer or licensee or`
  line `lessee in this behalf, give to him a certificate for collection of tax at such lower rate than the relevant rate`
  line `specified in sub-section ( 1 ) 9 [or sub-section ( 1C )] 10 ***.`
  line `( 10 ) Where a certificate under sub-section ( 9 ) is given, the person responsible for collecting the tax`
  line `shall, until such certificate is cancelled by the Assessing Officer, collect the tax at the rates specified in`
  line `such certificate.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 81, for “Provided that” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 47, for “seller” (w.e..f 1 -4-2007).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 9, for “one and one -fourth per cent." (w.e.f. 8-9-2003).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-6-2006).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 81 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `6. The words “, other than a person referred to in sub -section ( 1D ),” omitted by Act 7 of 2017, s. 72 (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 80 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 50, for “buyer” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2004).`
  line `9. Ins. by s. 50, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-2004).`
  line `10. The words “or sub -section ( 1D )” omitted by Act 7 of 2017, s. 72 (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
