obj_root_law_sections_673_content:
  string
  line 673
  line `( 11 ) The Board may, having regard to the convenience of assessees and the interests of revenue, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules specifying the cases in which, and the circumstances under`
  line `which, an application may be made for the grant of a certificate under sub-section ( 9 ) and the conditions`
  line `subject to which such certificate may be granted and providing for all other matters connected therewith.]`
  line `1 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `2 [( a ) “accountant” shall have the meaning assigned to it in the Explanation to sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 288;`
  line `( aa ) “buyer” with respect to—`
  line `( i ) sub-section ( 1 ) means a person who obtains in any sale, by way of auction, tender or any`
  line `other mode, goods of the nature specified in the Table in sub-section ( 1 ) or the right to receive`
  line `any such goods but does not include, —`
  line `( A ) a public sector company, the Central Government, a State Government, and an`
  line `embassy, a High Commission, legation, commission, consulate and the trade representation,`
  line `of a foreign State and a club; or`
  line `( B ) a buyer in the retail sale of such goods purchased by him for personal consumption;`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 [( iii ) sub-section ( 1F ) means a person who obtains in any sale, goods of the nature specified`
  line `in the said sub-section, but does not include, —`
  line `( A ) the Central Government, a State Government and an embassy, a High Commission,`
  line `legation, commission, consulate and the trade representation of a foreign State; or`
  line `( B ) a local authority as defined in Explanation to clause ( 20 ) of section 10; or`
  line `( C ) a public sector company which is engaged in the business of carrying passengers.]`
  line `5 * * * * *]`
  line `6 [( b ) “scrap” means waste and scrap from the manufacture or mechanical working of materials`
  line `which is definitely not usable as such because of breakage, cutting up, wear and other reasons;]`
  line `( c ) “seller” means the Central Government, a State Government or any local authority or`
  line `corporation or authority established by or under a Central, State or Provincial Act, or any company or`
  line `firm or co-operative society and also includes an individual or a Hindu undivided family whose total`
  line `sales, gross receipts or turnover from the business or profession carried on by him exceed the`
  line `monetary limits specified under clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of section 44AB during the financial`
  line `yearimmediately preceding the financial year in which the goods of the nature specified in the Table`
  line `in sub-section ( 1 ) 7 [are sold].`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 79 (w.e.f. 1-4-1992).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 81, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `3. Sub-clause ( ii ) omitted by Act 7 of 2017, s. 72 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 72, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `5. Clause ( ab ) omitted by s. 72, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 87, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 72, for “ or sub-section ( 1D ) are sold or services referred to in sub-section ( 1D ) are provided”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
