obj_root_law_sections_675_content:
  string
  line 675
  line `( ii ) in respect of rate of collection of tax at source, where such rate is not in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) The Board may make a scheme for centralised processing of statements of tax collected at source`
  line `to expeditiously determine the tax payable by, or the refund due to, the collector, as required under sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ).]`
  line `1 [ 206CC. Requirement to furnish Permanent Account number by collectee. — ( 1 )`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provisions of this Act, any person paying any sum or`
  line `amount, on which tax is collectible at source under Chapter XVII-BB (herein referred to as collectee)`
  line `shall furnish his Permanent Account Number to the person responsible for collecting such tax (herein`
  line `referred to as collector), failing which tax shall be collected at the higher of the following rates,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( i ) at twice the rate specified in the relevant provision of this Act; or`
  line `( ii ) at the rate of five per cent.`
  line `( 2 ) No declaration under sub-section ( 1A ) of section 206C shall be valid unless the person furnishes`
  line `his Permanent Account Number in such declaration.`
  line `( 3 ) In case any declaration becomes invalid under sub-section ( 2 ), the collector shall collect the tax at`
  line `source in accordance with the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 4 ) No certificate under sub-section ( 9 ) of section 206C shall be granted unless the application made`
  line `under that section contains the Permanent Account Number of the applicant.`
  line `( 5 ) The collectee shall furnish his Permanent Account Number to the collector and both shall indicate`
  line `the same in all the correspondence, bills, vouchers and other documents which are sent to each other.`
  line `( 6 ) Where the Permanent Account Number provided to the collector is invalid or does not belong to`
  line `the collectee, it shall be deemed that the collectee has not furnished his Permanent Account Number to`
  line `the collector and the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) shall apply accordingly.`
  line `( 7 ) The provisions of this section shall not apply to a non-resident who does not have permanent`
  line `establishment in India.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- section, the expression “permanent establishment”`
  line `includes a fixed place of business through which the business of the enterprise is wholly or partly carried`
  line `on. ]`
  line `2 [ 207. Liability for payment of advance tax. — 3 [( 1 )] Tax shall be payable in advance during any`
  line `financial year, in accordance with the provisions of sections 208 to 219 (both inclusive), in respect of the`
  line `total income of the assessee which would be chargeable to tax for the assessment year immediately`
  line `following that financial year, such income being hereafter in this Chapter referred to as “current income”.`
  line `4 [( 2 ) The provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) shall not apply to an individual resident in India, who —`
  line `( a ) does nothave any income chargeable under the head “Profits and gains of business or`
  line `profession”; and`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 73 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 76, for sections 207 and 208 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988). Earlier amended by Act 16 of 1972, s. 33 (w.e.f.`
  line `1-4-1972).`
  line `3. Section207 renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 23 of 2012, s. 82 (w.e.f. 1-4-2012).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 82, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2012).`
