obj_root_law_sections_676_content:
  string
  line 676
  line `( b ) is of the age of sixty years or more at any time during the previous year.]`
  line `208. Conditions of liability to pay advance tax. — Advance tax shall be payable during a financial`
  line `year in every case where the amount of such tax payable by the assessee during that year, as computed in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Chapter, is ten thousand rupees or more.]`
  line `209.Computation of advance tax. — 1 [( 1 ) The amount of advance tax payable by an assessee in the`
  line `financial year shall, subject to the provisions of sub-sections ( 2 ) and ( 3 ), be computed as follows,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( a ) where the calculation is made by the assessee for the purposes of payment of advance tax`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-section ( 5 ) or sub-section ( 6 ) of section 210, he shall`
  line `first estimate his current income and income-tax thereon shall be calculated at the rates in force in the`
  line `financial year;`
  line `( b ) where the calculation is made by the Assessing Officer for the purpose of making an order`
  line `under sub-section ( 3 ) of section 210, the total income of the latest previous year in respect of which`
  line `the assessee has been assessed by way of regular assessment or the total income returned by the`
  line `assessee in any return of income furnished by him for any subsequent previous year, whichever is`
  line `higher, shall be taken and income-tax thereon shall be calculated at the rates in force in the financial`
  line year;
  line `( c ) where the calculation is made by the Assessing Officer for the purpose of making an`
  line `amended order under sub-section (4) of section 210, the total income declared in the return furnished`
  line `by the assessee for the later previous year, or, as the case may be, the total income in respect of which`
  line `the regular assessment, referred to in that sub-section has been made, shall be taken and income-tax`
  line `thereon shall be calculated at the rates in force in the financial year;`
  line `( d ) the income-tax calculated under clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ) shall, in each case, be`
  line `reduced by the amount of income-tax which would be 2 [deductible or collectible at source] during the`
  line `said financial year under any provision of this Act from any income (as computed before allowing`
  line `any deductions admissible under this Act) which has been taken into account in computing the`
  line `current income or, as the case may be, the total income aforesaid; and the amount of income-tax as so`
  line `reduced shall be the advance tax payable:]`
  line `3 [Provided that for computing liability for advance tax, income-tax calculated under clause ( a ) or`
  line `clause ( b ) or clause ( c ) shall not, in each case, be reduced by the aforesaid amount of income-tax`
  line `which would be deductible or collectible at source during the said financial year under any provision`
  line `of this Act from any income, if the person responsible for deducting tax has paid or credited such`
  line `income without deduction of tax or it has been received or debited by the person responsible for`
  line `collecting tax without collection of such tax.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 77, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 35, for “deductible at source” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 83 (w.e.f. 1-4-2012).`
