obj_root_law_sections_677_content:
  string
  line 677
  line `1 [( 2 ) Where the Finance Act of the relevant year provides that, in the case of any class of assessees,`
  line `net agricultural income (as defined in that Act) shall be taken into account for the purposes of computing`
  line `advance tax, then, the net agricultural income to be taken into account in the case of any assessee falling`
  line `in that class, shall be —`
  line `( a ) in cases 2 [where the Assessing Officer makes an order under sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section`
  line `( 4 ) of section 210], —`
  line `( i ) if the total income of the latest previous year in respect of which the assessee has been`
  line `assessed by way of regular assessment forms the basis of computation of advance tax payable by him,`
  line `the net agricultural income which has been taken into account for the purposes of charging income-`
  line `tax for the assessment year relevant to that previous year; or`
  line `3 [( ii ) if the total income declared by the assessee for the later previous year referred to in sub-`
  line `section ( 4 ) of section 210 forms the basis of computation of advance tax, the net agricultural income`
  line `as returned by the assessee in the return of income for the assessment year relevant to such later`
  line `previous year;]`
  line `4 [( b ) in cases where the advance tax is paid by the assessee on the basis of his estimate of his current`
  line `income under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-section ( 5 ) or sub-section ( 6 ) of section 210, the`
  line `net agricultural income, as estimated by him, of the period which would be the previous year for the`
  line `immediately following assessment year.]`
  line `( 3 ) Where the Finance Act of the relevant year specifies any separate rate or rates for the purposes of`
  line `computing advance tax in the case of every Hindu undivided family which has at least one member whose`
  line `total income of the previous year exceeds the maximum amount not chargeable to income-tax in his case,`
  line `then, the 5 [Assessing Officer] shall, for making an order under 6 [sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 4 )`
  line `of section 210] in the case of any such Hindu undivided family, compute (subject to the provisions`
  line `of section 164) the advance tax at such rate or rates —`
  line `( a ) in a case where the total income of the latest previous year in respect of which the Hindu`
  line `undivided family has been assessed by way of regular assessment forms the basis of computation of`
  line `advance tax, if the total income of any member of the family for the assessment year relevant to such`
  line `latest previous year exceeds the maximum amount not chargeable to income-tax in his case;`
  line `( b ) in a case where the total income of the previous year 7 [in respect of which a return of income is`
  line `furnished by the Hindu undivided family under section 139 or in response to a notice under sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) of section 142] forms the basis of computation of advance tax, if the total income of any member of`
  line `the family for the assessment year relevant to such previous year exceeds the maximum amount not`
  line `chargeable to income-tax in his case.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 1974, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 77, for “where the assessee sends a statement under sub -section ( 1 ) of section 209A or where`
  line `the Income-tax Officer makes an order under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 3 ) of section 210” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 77, ibid., for sub-clause ( ii ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 77, ibid., for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 77, ibid., for “under section 210” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 77, ibid., for “on the basis of which tax has been paid by the Hindu undivided family under section 140A”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
