obj_root_law_sections_678_content:
  string
  line 678
  line `209A. [Computation and payment of advance tax by assessee.] Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws`
  line `( Amendment ) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988), s. 78 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988). Original section was inserted by the Finance`
  line `Act, 1978 (19 of 1978), s. 24 ( w.e.f. 1-6-1978).`
  line `1 [ 210. Payment of advance tax by the assessee of his own accord or in pursuance of order of`
  line `Assessing Officer. — ( 1 ) Every person who is liable to pay advance tax under section 208 (whether or not`
  line `he has been previously assessed by way of regular assessment) shall, of his own accord, pay, on or before`
  line `each of the due dates specified in section 211, the appropriate percentage, specified in that section, of the`
  line `advance tax on his current income, calculated in the manner laid down in section 209.`
  line `( 2 ) A person who pays any instalment or instalments of advance tax under sub-section ( 1 ), may`
  line `increase or reduce the amount of advance tax payable in the remaining instalment or instalments to accord`
  line `with his estimate of his current income and the advance tax payable thereon, and make payment of the`
  line `said amount in the remaining instalment or instalments accordingly.`
  line `( 3 ) In the case of a person who has been already assessed by way of regular assessment in respect of`
  line `the total income of any previous year, 2 *** the Assessing Officer, if he is of opinion that such person is`
  line `liable to pay advance tax, may, at any time during the financial year but not later than the last day of`
  line `February, by order in writing, require such person to pay advance tax calculated in the manner laid down`
  line `in section 209, and issue to such person a notice of demand under section 156 specifying the instalment or`
  line `instalments in which such tax is to be paid.`
  line `( 4 ) If, after the making of an order by the Assessing Officer under sub-section ( 3 ) and at any time`
  line `before the 1st day of March, a return of income is furnished by the assessee under section 139 or in`
  line `response to a notice under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142, or a regular assessment of the assessee is made`
  line `in respect of a previous year later than that referred to in sub-section ( 3 ), the Assessing Officer may make`
  line `an amended order and issue to such assessee a notice of demand under section 156 requiring the assessee`
  line `to pay, on or before the due date or each of the due dates specified in section 211falling after the date of`
  line `the amended order, the appropriate percentage, specified in section 211, of the advance tax computed on`
  line `the basis of the total income declared in such return or in respect of which the regular assessment`
  line `aforesaid has been made.`
  line `( 5 ) A person who is served with an order of the Assessing Officer under sub-section ( 3 ) or an`
  line `amended order under sub-section ( 4 ) may, if in his estimation the advance tax payable on his current`
  line `income would be less than the amount of the advance tax specified in such order or amended order, send`
  line `an intimation in the prescribed form to the Assessing Officer to that effect and pay such advance tax as`
  line `accords with his estimate, calculated in the manner laid down in section 209, at the appropriate`
  line `percentage thereof specified in section 211, on or before the due date or each of the due dates specified`
  line `in section 211 falling after the date of such intimation.`
  line `( 6 ) A person who is served with an order of the Assessing Officer under sub-section ( 3 ) or amended`
  line `order under sub-section ( 4 ) shall, if in his estimation the advance tax payable on his current income would`
  line `exceed the amount of advance tax specified in such order or amended order or intimated by him under`
  line `sub-section ( 5 ), pay on or before the due date of the last instalment specified in section 211, the`
  line `appropriate part or, as the case may be, the whole of such higher amount of advance tax as accords with`
  line `his estimate, calculated in the manner laid down in section 209.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 79, for section 210 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. The words “and who has not paid any advance tax under sub -section ( 1 )” omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 92 (w.e.f. 1-6-`
  line `2002).`
