obj_root_law_sections_679_content:
  string
  line 679
  line `1 [ 211. Instalments of advance tax and due dates. — 2 [( 1 ) Advance tax on the current income`
  line `calculated in the manner laid down in section 209 shall be payable by —`
  line `( a ) all the assessees, other than the assessee referred to in clause ( b ), who are liable to pay the`
  line `same, in four instalments during each financial year and the due date of each instalment and`
  line `theamount of such instalment shall be as specified in the Table below:`
  line TABLE
  line `( b ) 3 [an assessee who declares profits and gains in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 44AD or sub-section ( 1 ) of section 44ADA, as the case may be], to the`
  line `extent of the whole amount of such advance tax during each financial year on or before the 15th`
  line `March:`
  line `Provided that any amount paid by way of advance tax on or before the 31st day of March shall also be`
  line `treated as advance tax paid during the financial year ending on that day for all the purposes of this Act.]`
  line `( 2 ) If the notice of demand issued under section 156 in pursuance of an order of the Assessing Officer`
  line `under sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 4 ) of section 210 is served after any of the due dates specified in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ), the appropriate part or, as the case may be, the whole of the amount of the advance tax`
  line `specified in such notice shall be payable on or before each of such of those dates as fall after the date of`
  line `service of the notice of demand.]`
  line `212. [Estimate by assessee.] Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988),`
  line `s. 81 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `213. [Commission receipts.] Omitted by s. 81, ibid. ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 80, for section 211 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 89, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 74, for “an eligible assessee in respect of an eligible business referred to in section 44AD”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `Due date of`
