obj_root_law_sections_680_content:
  string
  line 680
  line `214. Interest payable by Government. — ( 1 ) The Central Government shall pay simple interest at`
  line `1 [fifteen per cent.] per annum on the amount by which the aggregate sum of any instalments of advance`
  line `tax paid during any financial year in which they are payable under sections 207 to 213 exceeds the`
  line `amount of the 2 [assessed tax] from the 1st day of April next following the said financial year to the date of`
  line `the regular assessment for the assessment year immediately following the said financial year, and where`
  line `any such instalment is paid after the expiry of the financial year, during which it is payable by reason of`
  line `the provisions of section 213, interest as aforesaid shall also be payable on that instalment from the date`
  line `of its payment to the date of regular assessment:`
  line `3 [Provided that in respect of any amount refunded on a provisional assessment under section 141A,`
  line `no interest shall be paid for any period after the date of such provisional assessment.]`
  line `4 [( 1A ) Where as a result of an order under section 147 or section 154 or section 155 or section`
  line `250 or section 254 or section 260 or section 262 or section 263 or section 264 5 [or an order of the`
  line `Settlement Commission under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 245D], the amount on which interest was`
  line `payable under sub-section ( 1 ) has been increased or reduced, as the case may be, the interest shall be`
  line `increased or reduced accordingly, and in a case where the interest is reduced, the 6 [Assessing Officer]`
  line `shall serve on the assessee, a notice of demand in the prescribed form specifying the amount of the excess`
  line `interest payable and requiring him to pay such amount; and such notice of demand shall be deemed to be`
  line `a notice under section 156 and the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly.]`
  line `( 2 ) On any portion of such amount which is refunded under this Chapter, interest shall be payable`
  line `only up to the date on which the refund was made.`
  line `7 [( 3 ) This section and sections 215, 216 and 217 shall not apply in respect of any assessment for the`
  line `assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1989, or any subsequent assessment year and, in the`
  line `application of the said sections to the assessment for any earlier assessment year, references therein`
  line `[except in sub-section ( 1A ) and sub-section ( 3 ) of section 215] to the other provisions of this Act shall be`
  line `construed as references to those provisions as for the time being in force and applicable to the relevant`
  line `assessment year.]`
  line `8 [ Explanation 1. —In this section, “assessed tax” shall have the same meaning as in sub -section ( 5 )`
  line `of section 215.`
  line `Explanation 2. — Where, in relation to an assessment year, an assessment is made for the first time`
  line `under section 147, the assessment so made shall be regarded as a regular assessment for the purposes of`
  line `this section.]`
  line `215. Interest payable by assessee. — 9 [( 1 )Where, in any financial year, an assessee has paid`
  line `10 [advance tax under section 209A or section 212 on the basis of his own estimate (including revised`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 24, for “twelve per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1984).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 35, ibid., for “tax determined on regular assessment” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1985).`
  line `3. Added by Act 19 of 1968, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-1968).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 35, for sub-section ( 1A ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 82 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. Ins. by s. 82, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 14 of 1969, s. 18, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-4-1970).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 19 of 1978, s. 27, for “advance tax under section 212 on the basis of his own estimate” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1978).`
