obj_root_law_sections_681_content:
  string
  line 681
  line `estimate)], and the advance tax so paid is less than seventy-five per cent. of the assessed tax, simple`
  line `interest at the rate of 1 [fifteen per cent.] per annum from the 1st day of April next following the said`
  line `financial year up to the date of the regular assessment shall be payable by the assessee upon the amount`
  line `by which the advance tax so paid falls short of the assessed tax:]`
  line `2 [Provided that in the case of an assessee, being a company, the provisions of this sub-section shall`
  line `have effect as if for the words “seventy - five per cent.”, the words “eighty -three and one- third per cent.”`
  line `had been substituted.]`
  line `3 [( 2 ) Where before the date of completion of a regular assessment, tax is paid by the assessee`
  line `under section 140A or otherwise, —`
  line `( i ) interest shall be calculated in accordance with the foregoing provision up to the date on which`
  line `the tax is so paid; and`
  line `( ii ) thereafter, interest shall be calculated at the rate aforesaid on the amount by which the tax as`
  line `so paid (in so far as it relates to income subject to advance tax) falls short of the assessed tax.]`
  line `4 [( 3 ) Where as a result of an order under section 147 or section 154 or section 155 or section`
  line `250 or section 254 or section 260 or section 262 or section 263 or section 264 5 [or an order of the`
  line `Settlement Commission under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 245D], the amount on which interest was`
  line `payable under sub-section ( 1 ) has been increased or reduced, as the case may be, the interest shall be`
  line `increased or reduced accordingly, and —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the interest is increased, the 6 [Assessing Officer] shall serve on the assessee, a`
  line `notice of demand in the prescribed form specifying the sum payable, and such notice of demand shall`
  line `be deemed to be a notice under section 156 and the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly;`
  line `( ii ) in a case where the interest is reduced, the excess interest paid, if any, shall be refunded.]`
  line `( 4 ) In such cases and under such circumstances as may be prescribed, the 6 [Assessing Officer] may`
  line `reduce or waive the interest payable by the assessee under this section.`
  line `7 [( 5 ) In this section and sections 217 and 273, “assessed tax” means the tax determined on the basis of`
  line `the regular assessment (reduced by the amount of tax deductible in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of sections 192 to 194, 8 [section 194A, section 194C] 9 [, section 194D] 10 [, section 195 and section`
  line `196A] so far as such tax relates to income subject to advance tax and so far as it is not due to variations in`
  line `the rates of tax made by the Finance Act enacted for the year for which the regular assessment is made.]`
  line `11 [( 6 ) Where, in relation to an assessment year, an assessment is made for the first time under section`
  line `147, the assessment so made shall be regarded as a regular assessment for the purposes of this section`
  line `and sections 216, 217 and 273.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 24, for “twelve per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1984).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-9-1980).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 37, for sub-section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 36, for sub-section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 83 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 14 of 1969, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-1970).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 38, for “section 194A” ( w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 21 of 1973, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 33, for “and section 195” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `11. Ins. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
