obj_root_law_sections_682_content:
  string
  line 682
  line `216. Interest payable by assessee in case of under-estimate, etc. — Where, on making the regular`
  line `assessment, the 1 [Assessing Officer] finds that any assessee has —`
  line `2 [( a ) under 3 [section 209A or section 212] under-estimated the advance tax payable by him and`
  line `thereby reduced the amount payable in either of the first two instalments; or`
  line `( b ) under section 213 wrongly deferred the payment of advance tax on a part of his income;`
  line `he may direct that the assessee shall pay simple interest at 4 [fifteen per cent.] per annum —`
  line `( i ) in the case referred to in clause ( a ), for the period during which the payment was deficient, on`
  line `the difference between the amount paid in each such instalment and the amount which should have`
  line `been paid, having regard to the aggregate advance tax actually paid during the year; and`
  line `( ii ) in the case referred to in clause ( b ), for the period during which the payment of advance tax`
  line `was so deferred.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, any instalment due before the expiry of six months`
  line `from the commencement of the previous year in respect of which it is to be paid shall be deemed to have`
  line `become due fifteen days after the expiry of the said six months.`
  line `217. Interest payable by assessee when no estimate made. — 5 [( 1 ) Where, on making the regular`
  line `assessment, 6 [the 1 [Assessing Officer] finds —`
  line `( a ) that any such person as is referred to in clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 209A has not`
  line `sent the statement referred to in that clause or the estimate in lieu of such statement referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of that section; or`
  line `( b ) that any such person as is referred to in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 209A has not`
  line `sent the estimate referred to in that clause,`
  line `simple interest at the rate of 4 [fifteen per cent.] per annum] from the 1st day of April next following the`
  line `financial year in which the advance tax was payable in accordance with 7 [the said sub-section ( 1 ) or`
  line `sub-section ( 2 )] up to the date of the regular assessment shall be payable by the assessee upon the amount`
  line `equal to the assessed tax as defined in sub-section ( 5 ) of section 215.`
  line `( 1A ) Where, on making the regular assessment, the 1 [Assessing Officer] finds that 8 [any person who`
  line `is required to send an estimate under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 209A or] any such person as is referred to`
  line `in sub-section ( 3A ) of section 212 has not sent the estimate referred to therein, simple interest at the rate`
  line `of 4 [fifteen per cent.] per annum from the 1st day of April next following the financial year in which the`
  line `advance tax was payable in accordance with 9 [the said sub-section ( 4 ) or, as the case may be, sub-section`
  line `( 3A )] up to the date of the regular assessment shall be payable by the assessee upon the amount by which`
  line `the advance tax paid by him falls short of the assessed tax as defined in sub-section ( 5 ) of section 215.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax officer” (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 14 of 1969, s. 19, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1970).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 19 of 1978, s. 28, for “sub -section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 3A ) of section`
  line `212” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1978).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 24, for “twelve per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1984). Earlier the quoted words were substituted by`
  line `Act 16 of 1972, s. 25 for “nine per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1972).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 14 of 1969, s. 20, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1970).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 19 of 1978, s. 29, for “the Income -tax Officer finds that any such person as is referred to in sub-section ( 3 )`
  line `of section 212 has not sent the estimate referred to therein, simple interest at the rate of twelve per cen t. per annum”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-6-1978).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 29, ibid., for “the said sub - section” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1978).`
  line `8. Ins. by s. 29, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-1978).`
  line `9. Subs. by s. 29, ibid., for “the said sub - section” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1978).`
