obj_root_law_sections_683_content:
  string
  line 683
  line `( 2 ) The provisions of sub-sections ( 2 ), ( 3 ) and ( 4 ) of section 215 shall apply to interest payable under`
  line `this section as they apply to interest payable under that section.`
  line `1 [ 218. When assessee deemed to be in default. — If any assessee does not pay on the date specified`
  line `in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 211, any instalment of the advance tax that he is required to pay by an order`
  line `of the Assessing Officer under sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 4 ) of section 210 and does not, on or before`
  line `the date on which any such instalment as is not paid becomes due, send to the Assessing Officer an`
  line `intimation under sub-section ( 5 ) of section 210 or does not pay on the basis of his estimate of his current`
  line `income the advance tax payable by him under sub-section ( 6 ) of section 210, he shall be deemed to be an`
  line `assessee in default in respect of such instalment or instalments.]`
  line `219. Credit for advance tax. — Any sum, other than a penalty or interest, paid by or recovered from`
  line `an assessee as advance tax in pursuance of this Chapter shall be treated as a payment of tax in respect of`
  line `the income of the period which would be the previous year for an assessment for the assessment year next`
  line `following the financial year in which it was payable, and credit therefor shall be given to the assessee in`
  line `the regular assessment.`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `D. — Collection and recovery`
  line `220. When tax payable and when assessee deemed in default. — ( 1 ) Any amount, otherwise than by`
  line `way of advance tax, specified as payable in a notice of demand under section 156 shall be paid within`
  line `3 [thirty days] of the service of the notice at the place and to the person mentioned in the notice:`
  line `Provided that, where the 4 [Assessing Officer] has any reason to believe that it will be detrimental to`
  line `revenue if the full period of 3 [thirty days] aforesaid is allowed, he may, with the previous approval of the`
  line `5 [Joint Commissioner], direct that the sum specified in the notice of demand shall be paid within such`
  line `period being a period less than the period of 3 [thirty days] aforesaid, as may be specified by him in the`
  line `notice of demand.`
  line `6 [( 1A ) Where any notice of demand has been served upon an assessee and any appeal or other`
  line `proceeding, as the case may be, is filed or initiated in respect of the amount specified in the said notice of`
  line `demand, then, such demand shall be deemed to be valid till the disposal of the appeal by the last appellate`
  line `authority or disposal of the proceedings, as the case may be, and any such notice of demand shall have the`
  line `effect as specified in section 3 of the Taxation Laws (Continuation and Validation of Recovery`
  line `Proceedings) Act, 1964 (11 of 1964).]`
  line `( 2 ) If the amount specified in any notice of demand under section 156 is not paid within the period`
  line `limited under sub-section ( 1 ), the assessee shall be liable to pay simple interest at 7 [ 8 [one per cent.] for`
  line `every month or part of a month comprised in the period commencing from the day immediately following`
  line `the end of the period mentioned in sub-section ( 1 ) and ending with the day on which the amount is paid]:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 84, for section 218 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988). Earlier section 218 was amended by Act 21 of 1979,`
  line `s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-1979) which was substituted by Act 19 of 1978, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-6-1978).`
  line `2. The proviso omitted by s. 126, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 85, ibid., for “thirty - five days” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 3, for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998). Earlier the quoted words were substituted`
  line `by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Inspecting Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 64 (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 85 for “fifteen per cent. per annum from the day commencing after the en d of the period`
  line `mentioned in sub-section ( 1 )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 10, for “one and one - fourth per cent.” (w.e.f. 8 -9-2003). Earlier the quoted words were subs.`
  line `by Act 14 of 2001, s. 76, for “one and one - half per cent.” (w.e.f. 1-6-2001).`
