obj_root_law_sections_684_content:
  string
  line 684
  line `1 [Provided that, where as a result of an order under section 154, or section 155, or section 250,`
  line `or section 254, or section 260, or section 262, or section 264 2 [or an order of the Settlement Commission`
  line `under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 245D], the amount on which interest was payable under this section had`
  line `been reduced, the interest shall be reduced accordingly and the excess interest paid, if any, shall be`
  line `refunded:]`
  line `3 [Provided further that where as a result of an order under sections specified in the first proviso, the`
  line `amount on which interest was payable under this section had been reduced and subsequently as a result of`
  line `an order under said sections or section 263, the amount on which interest was payable under this section`
  line `is increased, the assessee shall be liable to pay interest under sub-section ( 2 ) from the day immediately`
  line `following the end of the period mentioned in the first notice of demand, referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) and`
  line `ending with the day on which the amount is paid:]`
  line `2 [ 4 [Provided also] that in respect of any period commencing on or before the 31st day of March, 1989`
  line `and ending after that date, such interest shall, in respect of so much of such period as falls after that date,`
  line `be calculated at the rate of one and one-half per cent for every month or part of a month.]`
  line `5 [( 2A ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 2 ), 6 [the 7 [ 8 [Principal Chief Commissioner`
  line `or Chief Commissioner] or 9 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] may] reduce or waive the`
  line `amount of 10 [interest paid or payable by an assessee] under the said sub-section if, 11 [he is satisfied]`
  line `that —`
  line `( i ) payment of such amount 12 [has caused or would cause genuine hardship] to the assessee;`
  line `( ii ) default in the payment of the amount on which 13 [interest has been paid or was payable] under`
  line `the said sub-section was due to circumstances beyond the control of the assessee; and`
  line `( iii ) theassessee has co-operated in any inquiry relating to the assessment or any proceeding for`
  line `the recovery of any amount due from him:]`
  line `14 [Provided that the order accepting or rejecting the application of the assessee, either in full or in`
  line `part, shall be passed within a period of twelve months from the end of the month in which the`
  line `application is received:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1963, s. 14 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 85 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 64 (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 64, ibid., for “Provided further” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2014).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 37 (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 13, for “the Board may” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1987).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Commisssioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
  line `9. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commisssioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 13, for “interest payable by an assessee” (w.r.e.f. 1 -10-1984).`
  line `11. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for “on the recommendation made by the Commissioner in this behalf, if is satisfied” (w.e.f. 1 -4-`
  line `1987).`
  line `12. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for “would cause genuine hardship” (w.r.e.f. 1 -10-1984).`
  line `13. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for “interest was payable” (w.r.e.f. 1 -10-1984).`
  line `14. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 90 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
