obj_root_law_sections_685_content:
  string
  line 685
  line `Provided further that no order rejecting the application, either in full or in part, shall be passed unless`
  line `the assessee has been given an opportunity of being heard:`
  line `Provided also that where any application is pending as on the 1st day of June, 2016, the order shall be`
  line `passed on or before the 31st day of May, 2017.]`
  line `1 [( 2B ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 2 ), where interest is charged under sub-`
  line `section ( 1A ) of section 201 on the amount of tax specified in the intimation issued under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 200A for any period, then, no interest shall be charged under sub-section ( 2 ) on the same`
  line `amount for the same period.]`
  line `2 [( 2C ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 2 ), where interest is charged under sub-`
  line `section ( 7 ) of section 206C on the amount of tax specified in the intimation issued under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 206CB for any period, then, no interest shall be charged under sub-section ( 2 ) on the same`
  line `amount for the same period.]`
  line `( 3 ) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section ( 2 ), on an application made by the`
  line `assessee before the expiry of the due date under sub-section ( 1 ), the 3 [Assessing Officer] may extend the`
  line `time for payment or allow payment by instalments, subject to such conditions as he may think fit to`
  line `impose in the circumstances of the case.`
  line `( 4 ) If the amount is not paid within the time limited under sub-section ( 1 ) or extended under sub-`
  line `section ( 3 ), as the case may be, at the place and to the person mentioned in the said notice the assessee`
  line `shall be deemed to be in default.`
  line `( 5 ) If, in a case where payment by instalments is allowed under sub-section ( 3 ), the assessee commits`
  line `defaults in paying any one of the instalments within the time fixed under that sub-section, the assessee`
  line `shall be deemed to be in default as to the whole of the amount then outstanding, and the other instalment`
  line `or instalments shall be deemed to have been due on the same date as the instalment actually in default.`
  line `( 6 ) Where an assessee has presented an appeal under section 246 4 [or section 246A] the 3 [Assessing`
  line `Officer] may, in his discretion and subject to such conditions as he may think fit to impose in the`
  line `circumstances of the case, treat the assessee as not being in default in respect of the amount in dispute in`
  line `the appeal, even though the time for payment has expired, as long as such appeal remains undisposed of.`
  line `( 7 ) Where an assessee has been assessed in respect of income arising outside India in a country the`
  line `laws of which prohibit or restrict the remittance of money to India, the 3 [Assessing Officer] shall not treat`
  line `the assessee as in default in respect of that part of the tax which is due in respect of that amount of his`
  line `income which, by reason of such prohibition or restriction, cannot be brought into India, and shall`
  line `continue to treat the assessee as not in default in respect of such part of the tax until the prohibition or`
  line `restriction is removed.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, income shall be deemed to have been brought into`
  line `India if it has been utilised or could have been utilised for the purposes of any expenditure actually`
  line `incurred by the assessee outside India or if the income, whether capitalised or not, has been brought into`
  line `India in any form.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 84 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 56 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 62 (w.e.f. 1-6-2000).`
