  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_686_footnotes
  sourcePage 686
obj_root_law_sections_686_content:
  string
  line 686
  line `221. Penalty payable when tax in default. — 1 [( 1 ) When an assessee is in default or is deemed to be`
  line `in default in making a payment of tax, he shall, in addition to the amount of the arrears and the amount of`
  line `interest payable under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 220, be liable, by way of penalty, to pay such amount as`
  line `the 2 [Assessing Officer] may direct, and in the case of a continuing default, such further amount or`
  line `amounts as the 2 [Assessing Officer] may, from time to time, direct, so, however, that the total amount of`
  line `penalty does not exceed the amount of tax in arrears:`
  line `Provided that before levying any such penalty, the assessee shall be given a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard:`
  line `3 [Provided further that where the assessee proves to the satisfaction of the 2 [Assessing Officer] that`
  line `the default was for good and sufficient reasons, no penalty shall be levied under this section.]]`
  line `4 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubt, it is hereby declared that an assessee shall not cease to be`
  line `liable to any penalty under this sub-section merely by reason of the fact that before the levy of such`
  line `penalty he has paid the tax.]`
  line `( 2 ) Where as a result of any final order the amount of tax, with respect to the default in the payment`
  line `of which the penalty was levied, has been wholly reduced, the penalty levied shall be cancelled and the`
  line `amount of penalty paid shall be refunded.`
  line `222. Certificate to Tax Recovery Officer. — ( 1 ) 5 [When an assessee is in default or is deemed to be`
  line `in default in making a payment of tax, the Tax Recovery Officer may draw up under his signature a`
  line `statement in the prescribed formspecifying the amount of arrears due from the assessee (such statement`
  line `being hereafter in this Chapter and in the Second S chedule referred to as “certificate”) and shall proceed`
  line `to recover from such assessee the amount specified in the certificate by one or more of the modes`
  line `mentioned below, in accordance with the rules laid down in the Second Schedule — ]`
  line `( a ) attachment and s ale of the assessee’s movable property;`
  line `( b ) attachment and sale of the assessee’s immovable property;`
  line `( c ) arrest of the assessee and his detention in prison;`
  line `( d ) appointing a receiver for the management of the assessee’s movable and immovable`
  line properties.
  line `6 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- section, the assessee’s movable or immovable property`
  line `shall include any property which has been transferred, directly or indirectly on or after the 1st day of`
  line `June, 1973, by the assessee to his spouse or minor child or son’s wife or son’s minor child, otherwise than`
  line `for adequate consideration, and which is held by, or stands in the name of, any of the persons aforesaid;`
  line `and so far as the movable or immovable property so transferred to his minor child o r his son’s minor child`
  line `is concerned, it shall, even after the date of attainment of majority by such minor child or son’s minor`
  line `child, as the case may be, continue to be included in the assessee’s movable or immovable property for`
  line `recovering any arrears due from the assessee in respect of any period prior to such date.]`
  line `7 [( 2 ) The Tax Recovery Officer may take action under sub-section ( 1 ), notwithstanding that`
  line `proceedings for recovery of the arrears by any other mode have been taken.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 38, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 14, for the second proviso (w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 53 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 86, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 54 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 86, for sub-section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
