obj_root_law_sections_687_content:
  string
  line 687
  line `1 [ 223. Tax Recovery Officer by whom recovery is to be effected. — ( 1 ) The Tax Recovery Officer`
  line `competent to take action under section 222 shall be —`
  line `( a ) the Tax Recovery Officer within whose jurisdiction the assessee carries on his business or`
  line `profession or within whose jurisdiction the principal place of his business or profession is situate, or`
  line `( b ) the Tax Recovery Officer within whose jurisdiction the assessee resides or any movable or`
  line `immovable property of the assessee is situate,`
  line `the jurisdiction for this purpose being the jurisdiction assigned to the Tax Recovery Officer under the`
  line `orders or directions issued by the Board, or by the 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner] or 3 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] who is authorised in this behalf by the`
  line `Board in pursuance of section 120.`
  line `( 2 ) Where an assessee has property within the jurisdiction of more than one Tax Recovery Officer`
  line `and the Tax Recovery Officer by whom the certificate is drawn up —`
  line `( a ) is not able to recover the entire amount by sale of the property, movable or immovable,`
  line `within his jurisdiction, or`
  line `( b ) is of the opinion that, for the purpose of expediting or securing the recovery of the whole or`
  line `any part of the amount under this Chapter, it is necessary so to do,`
  line `he may send the certificate or, where only a part of the amount is to be recovered, a copy of the certificate`
  line `certified in the prescribed mannerand specifying the amount to be recovered to a Tax Recovery Officer`
  line `within whose jurisdiction the assessee resides or has property and, thereupon, that Tax Recovery Officer`
  line `shall also proceed to recover the amount under this Chapter as if the certificate or copy thereof had been`
  line `drawn up by him.`
  line `224. Validity of certificate and cancellation or amendment thereof. — It shall not be open to the`
  line `assessee to dispute the correctness of any certificate drawn up by the Tax Recovery Officer on any ground`
  line `whatsoever, but it shall be lawful for the Tax Recovery Officer to cancel the certificate if, for any reason,`
  line `he thinks it necessary so to do, or to correct any clerical or arithmetical mistake therein.`
  line `225. Stay of proceedings in pursuance of certificate and amendment or cancellation`
  line `thereof. — ( 1 ) It shall be lawful for the Tax Recovery Officer to grant time for the payment of any tax and`
  line `when he does so, he shall stay the proceedings for the recovery of such tax until the expiry of the time so`
  line granted.
  line `( 2 ) Where the order giving rise to a demand of tax for which a certificate has been drawn up is`
  line `modified in appeal or other proceeding under this Act, and, as a consequence thereof, the demand is`
  line `reduced but the order is the subject-matter of further proceeding under this Act, the Tax Recovery Officer`
  line `shall stay the recovery of such part of the amount specified in the certificate as pertains to the said`
  line `reduction for the period for which the appeal or other proceeding remains pending.`
  line `( 3 ) Where a certificate has been drawn up and subsequently the amount of the outstanding demand is`
  line `reduced as a result of an appeal or other proceeding under this Act, the Tax Recovery Officer shall, when`
  line `the order which was the subject-matter of such appeal or other proceeding has become final and`
  line `conclusive, amend the certificate, or cancel it, as the case may be.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 87, for sections 223, 224 and 225 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
