  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_688_footnotes
  sourcePage 688
obj_root_law_sections_688_content:
  string
  line 688
  line `226. Other modes of recovery. — 1 [( 1 ) Where no certificate has been drawn up under section 222, the`
  line `Assessing Officer may recover the tax by any one or more of the modes provided in this section.`
  line `( 1A ) Where a certificate has been drawn up under section 222, the Tax Recovery Officer may,`
  line `without prejudice to the modes of recovery specified in that section, recover the tax by any one or more of`
  line `the modes provided in this section.]`
  line `( 2 ) If any assessee is in receipt of any income chargeable under the head “Salaries”, the 2 [Assessing`
  line `Officer] 3 [or Tax Recovery Officer] may require any person paying the same to deduct from any payment`
  line `subsequent to the date of such requisition any arrears of tax due from such assessee, and such person shall`
  line `comply with any such requisition and shall pay the sum so deducted to the credit of the Central`
  line `Government or as the Board directs:`
  line `Provided that any part of the salary exempt from attachment in execution of a decree of a civil court`
  line `under section 60 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), shall be exempt from any requisition`
  line `made under this sub-section.`
  line `( 3 ) ( i ) The 2 [Assessing Officer] 3 [or Tax Recovery Officer] may, at any time or from time to time, by`
  line `notice in writing require any person from whom money is due or may become due to the assessee or any`
  line `person who holds or may subsequently hold money for or on account of the assessee to pay to the`
  line `2 [Assessing Officer] 3 [or Tax Recovery Officer] either forthwith upon the money becoming due or being`
  line `held or at or within the time specified in the notice (not being before the money becomes due or is held)`
  line `so much of the money as is sufficient to pay the amount due by the assessee in respect of arrears or the`
  line `whole of the money when it is equal to or less than that amount.`
  line `( ii ) A notice under this sub-section may be issued to any person who holds or may subsequently hold`
  line `any money for or on account of the assessee jointly with any other person and for the purposes of this`
  line `sub-section, the shares of the joint holders in such account shall be presumed, until the contrary is proved,`
  line `to be equal.`
  line `( iii ) A copy of the notice shall be forwarded to the assessee at his last address known to the`
  line `2 [Assessing Officer] 3 [or Tax Recovery Officer], and in the case of a joint account to all the joint holders`
  line `at their last addresses known to the 2 [Assessing Officer] 3 [or Tax Recovery Officer].`
  line `( iv ) Save as otherwise provided in this sub-section, every person to whom a notice is issued under this`
  line `sub-section shall be bound to comply with such notice, and, in particular, where any such notice is issued`
  line `to a post office, banking company or an insurer, it shall not be necessary for any pass book, deposit`
  line `receipt, policy or any other document to be produced for the purpose of any entry, endorsement or the like`
  line `being made before payment is made, notwithstanding any rule, practice or requirement to the contrary.`
  line `( v ) Any claim respecting any property in relation to which a notice under this sub-section has been`
  line `issued arising after the date of the notice shall be void as against any demand contained in the notice.`
  line `( vi ) Where a person to whom a notice under this sub-section is sent objects to it by a statement on`
  line `oath that the sum demanded or any part thereof is not due to the assessee or that he does not hold any`
  line `money for or on account of the assessee, then nothing contained in this sub-section shall be deemed to`
  line `require such person to pay any such sum or part thereof, as the case may be, but if it is discovered that`
  line `such statement was false in any material particular, such person shall be personally liable to the`
  line `2 [Assessing Officer] 3 [or Tax Recovery Officer] to the extent of his own liability to the assessee on the`
  line `date of the notice, or to the extent of the assessee’s liability for any sum due under this Act, whichever is`
  line less.
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 88, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 36, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 37, ibid (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
