obj_root_law_sections_689_content:
  string
  line 689
  line `( vii ) The 1 [Assessing Officer] 2 [or Tax Recovery Officer] may, at any time or from time to time,`
  line `amend or revoke any notice issued under this sub-section or extend the time for making any payment in`
  line `pursuance of such notice.`
  line `( viii ) The 1 [Assessing Officer] 2 [or Tax Recovery Officer] shall grant a receipt for any amount paid in`
  line `compliance with a notice issued under this sub-section, and the person so paying shall be fully discharged`
  line `from his liability to the assessee to the extent of the amount so paid.`
  line `( ix ) Any person discharging any liability to the assessee after receipt of a notice under this sub-section`
  line `shall be personally liable to the 1 [Assessing Officer] 2 [or Tax Recovery Officer] to the extent of his own`
  line `liability to the assessee so discharged or to the extent of the assessee’s liability for any sum due under this`
  line `Act, whichever is less.`
  line `( x ) If the person to whom a notice under this sub-section is sent fails to make payment in pursuance`
  line `thereof to the 1 [Assessing Officer] 2 [or Tax Recovery Officer], he shall be deemed to be an assessee in`
  line `default in respect of the amount specified in the notice and further proceedings may be taken against him`
  line `for the realisation of the amount as if it were an arrear of tax due from him, in the manner provided`
  line `in sections 222 to 225 and the notice shall have the same effect as an attachment of a debt by the Tax`
  line `Recovery Officer in exercise of his powers under section 222.`
  line `( 4 ) The 1 [Assessing Officer] 2 [or Tax Recovery Officer] may apply to the court in whose custody`
  line `there is money belonging to the assessee for payment to him of the entire amount of such money, or, if it`
  line `is more than the tax due, an amount sufficient to discharge the tax.`
  line `3 [( 5 ) The 1 [Assessing Officer] 2 [or Tax Recovery Officer] may, if so authorised by the 4 [ 5 [Principal`
  line `Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 6 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] by general`
  line `or special order, recover any arrears of tax due from an assessee by distraint and sale of his movable`
  line `property in the manner laid down in the Third Schedule.]`
  line `227. Recovery through State Government. — If the recovery of tax in any area has been entrusted to`
  line `a State Government under clause ( 1 ) of article 258 of the Constitution, the State Government may direct,`
  line `with respect to that area or any part thereof; that tax shall be recovered therein with, and as an addition to,`
  line `any municipal tax or local rate, by the same person and in the same manner as the municipal tax or local`
  line `rate is recovered.`
  line `228. [Recovery of Indian tax in Pakistan and Pakistan tax in India.] Omitted by the Direct Tax`
  line `Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988), s. 89 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `7 [228A. Recovery of tax in pursuance of agreements with foreign countries. — ( 1 ) Where an`
  line `agreement is entered into by the Central Government with the Government of any country outside India`
  line `for recovery of income-tax under this Act and the corresponding law in force in that country and the`
  line `Government of that country or any authority under that Government which is specified in this behalf in`
  line `such agreement sends to the Board a certificate for the recovery of any tax due under such corresponding`
  line `law from a person having any property in India, the Board may forward such certificate to any Tax`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 36, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 37, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 54, for sub-section ( 5 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 39 (w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
obj_root_law_sections_689_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_690:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-690
