  title `Page 690`
  content obj_root_law_sections_690_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_690_footnotes
  sourcePage 690
obj_root_law_sections_690_content:
  string
  line 690
  line `Recovery Officer within whose jurisdiction such property is situated and thereupon such Tax Recovery`
  line `Officer shall —`
  line `( a ) proceed to recover the amount specified in the certificate in the manner in which he would`
  line `proceed to recover the amount 1 [specified in a certificate drawn up by him under section 222]; and`
  line `( b ) remit any sum so recovered by him to the Board after deducting his expenses in connection`
  line `with the recovery proceedings.`
  line `2 [( 2 ) Where an assessee is in default or is deemed to be in default in making a payment of tax, the Tax`
  line `Recovery Officer may, if the assessee has property in a country outside India (being a country with which`
  line `the Central Government has entered into an agreement for the recovery of income-tax under this Act and`
  line `the corresponding law in force in that country), forward to the Board a certificate drawn up by him`
  line `under section 222 and the Board may take such action thereon as it may deem appropriate having regard`
  line `to the terms of the agreement with such country.]]`
  line `229. Recovery of penalties, fine, interest and other sums. — Any sum imposed by way of interest,`
  line `fine, penalty, or any other sum payable under the provisions of this Act, shall be recoverable in the`
  line `manner provided in this Chapter for the recovery of arrears of tax.`
  line `230. Tax clearance certificate. — 3 [( 1 ) Subject to such exceptions as the Central Government may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf, no person, —`
  line `( a ) who is not domiciled in India;`
  line `( b ) who has come to India in connection with business, profession or employment; and`
  line `( c ) who has income derived from any source in India,`
  line `shall leave the territory of India by land, sea or air unless he furnishes to such authorityas may be`
  line `prescribed —`
  line `( i ) an undertaking in the prescribed formfrom his employer; or`
  line `( ii ) through whom such person is in receipt of the income,`
  line `to the effect that tax payable by such person who is not domiciled in India shall be paid by the employer`
  line `referred to in clause ( i ) or the person referred to in clause ( ii ), and the prescribed authorityshall, on receipt`
  line `of the undertaking, immediately give to such person a no objection certificate, for leaving India:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in sub-section ( 1 ) shall apply to a person who is not domiciled in`
  line `India but visits India as a foreign tourist or for any other purpose not connected with business, profession`
  line `or employment.`
  line `( 1A ) Subject to such exceptions as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify in this behalf, every person, who is domiciled in India at the time of his departure from`
  line `India, shall furnish, in the prescribed formto the income-tax authority or such other authority as may be`
  line `prescribed —`
  line `( a ) the permanent account number allotted to him under section 139A:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 90, for “specified in a certificate received from an Assessing Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 90, ibid., for sub-section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 88, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_690_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_691:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-691
  sectionNo (691)
  orderNo 691
  title `Page 691`
  content obj_root_law_sections_691_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_691_footnotes
  sourcePage 691
obj_root_law_sections_691_content:
  string
  line 691
  line `Provided that in case no such permanent account number has been allotted to him, or his total`
  line `income is not chargeable to income-tax or he is not required to obtain a permanent account number`
  line `under this Act, such person shall furnish a certificate in the prescribed form;`
  line `( b ) the purpose of his visit outside India;`
  line `( c ) the estimated period of his stay outside India:`
  line `Provided that no person —`
  line `( i ) who is domiciled in India at the time of his departure; and`
  line `( ii ) in respect of whom circumstances exist which, in the opinion of an income-tax authority`
  line `render it necessary for such person to obtain a certificate under this section,`
  line `shall leave the territory of India by land, sea or air unless he obtains a certificate from the income-tax`
  line `authority stating that he has no liabilities under this Act, or the Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957), or the`
  line `Gift-tax Act, 1958 (18 of 1958), or the Expenditure-tax Act, 1987 (35 of 1987), or that satisfactory`
  line `arrangements have been made for the payment of all or any of such taxes which are or may become`
  line `payable by that person:`
  line `Provided that no income-tax authority shall make it necessary for any person who is domiciled in`
  line `India to obtain a certificate under this section unless he records the reasons therefor and obtains the prior`
  line `approval of the 1 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] of Income-tax.]`
  line `( 2 ) If the owner or charterer of any ship or aircraft carrying persons from any place in the territory of`
  line `India to any place outside India allows any person to whom sub-section ( 1 ) 2 [or the first proviso to`
  line `sub-section ( 1A )] applies to travel by such ship or aircraft without first satisfying himself that such person`
  line `is in possession of a certificate as required by that sub-section, he shall be personally liable to pay the`
  line `whole or any part of the amount of tax, if any, payable by such person as the 3 [Assessing Officer] may,`
  line `having regard to the circumstances of the case, determine.`
  line `( 3 ) In respect of any sum payable by the owner or charterer of any ship or aircraft under`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ), the owner or charterer, as the case may be, shall be deemed to be an assessee in default`
  line `for such sum, and such sum shall be recoverable from him in the manner provided in this Chapter as if it`
  line `were an arrear of tax.`
  line `( 4 ) The Board may make rules for regulating any matter necessary for, or incidental to, the purpose of`
  line `carrying out the provisions of this section.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, the expressions “owner” and “charterer” include any`
  line `representative, agent or employee empowered by the owner or charterer to allow persons to travel by the`
  line `ship or aircraft.`
  line `230A. [Restrictions on registration of transfers of immovable property in certain`
  line `cases.] — Omitted by the Finance Act, 2001 (14 of 2001), s. 77 ( w.e.f. 1-6-2001).`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
