obj_root_law_sections_692_content:
  string
  line 692
  line `231. [Period for commencing recovery proceedings.] — Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws`
  line `( Amendment ) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988), s. 93 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `232. Recovery by suit or under other law not affected. — The several modes of recovery specified`
  line `in this Chapter shall not affect in any way —`
  line `( a ) any other law for the time being in force relating to the recovery of debts due to Government;`
  line or
  line `( b ) the right of the Government to institute a suit for the recovery of the arrears due from the`
  line assessee;
  line `and it shall be lawful for the 1 [Assessing Officer] or the Government, as the case may be, to have recourse`
  line `to any such law or suit, notwithstanding that the tax due is being recovered from the assessee by any`
  line `mode specified in this Chapter.`
  line `E. — Tax payable under provisional assessment`
  line `233. [ Recovery of tax payable under provisional assessment.] — Omitted by the Taxation Laws`
  line `( Amendment ) Act, 1970 (42 of 1970), s. 39 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `234. [ Tax paid by deduction or advance payment.] — Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 1987 (4 of 1988), s. 126 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2 [ F. — Interest chargeable in certain cases`
  line `234A.Interest for defaults in furnishing return of income. — ( 1 ) Where the return of income for`
  line `any assessment year under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 4 ) of section 139, or in response to a notice`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142, is furnished after the due date, or is not furnished, the assessee shall`
  line `be liable to pay simple interest at the rate of 3 [one per cent.] for every month or part of a month comprised`
  line `in the period commencing on the date immediately following the due date, and, —`
  line `( a ) where the return is furnished after the due date, ending on the date of furnishing of the return;`
  line or
  line `( b ) where no return has been furnished, ending on the date of completion of the assessment under`
  line `section 144,`
  line `4 [on the amount of the tax on the total income as determined under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143, and`
  line `where a regular assessment is made, on the amount of the tax on the total income determined under`
  line `regular assessment, as reduced by the amount of, —`
  line `( i ) advance tax, if any, paid;`
  line `( ii ) any tax deducted or collected at source;`
  line `( iii ) any relief of tax allowed under section 90 on account of tax paid in a country outside India;`
  line `( iv ) any relief of tax allowed under section 90A on account of tax paid in a specified territory`
  line `outside India referred to in that section;`
  line `( v ) any deduction, from the Indian income-tax payable, allowed under section 91, on account of`
  line `tax paid in a country outside India; and`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 94, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 12, for “one and one - fourth per cent.” (w.e.f. 8 -9-2003). Earlier substitution by Act 27 of`
  line `1999, s. 81 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 48, for "on the amount of the tax on the total income as determined under sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 143 or on regular assessment as reduced by the advance tax, if any, paid and any tax deducted or collected at`
  line `source" (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).Earlier were amended by 3 of 1989, s. 38 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
