obj_root_law_sections_693_content:
  string
  line 693
  line `( vi ) any tax credit allowed to be set off in accordance with the provisions of section`
  line `115JAA 1 [or section 115JD].]`
  line `Explanation 1. —In this section, “due date” means the date specified in sub -section ( 1 ) of section`
  line `139 as applicable in the case of the assessee.`
  line `2 [ Explanation 2. — In this sub-section, "tax on the total income as determined under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 143" shall not include the additional income-tax, if any, payable under section 143.]`
  line `Explanation 3. — Where, in relation to an assessment year, an assessment is made for the first time`
  line `3 [under section 147 or section 153A], the assessment so made shall be regarded as a regular assessment`
  line `for the purposes of this section.`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `( 2 ) The interest payable under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be reduced by the interest, if any, paid`
  line `under section 140A towards the interest chargeable under this section.`
  line `( 3 ) Where the return of income for any assessment year, required 3 [by a notice under section`
  line `148 or section 153A] issued 5 [after the determination of income under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143 or]`
  line `after the completion of an assessment under sub-section ( 3 ) of section 143 or section 144 or section 147,`
  line `is furnished after the expiry of the time allowed under such notice, or is not furnished, the assessee shall`
  line `be liable to pay simple interest at the rate of 6 [one per cent.] for every month or part of a month comprised`
  line `in the period commencing on the day immediately following the expiry of the time allowed as aforesaid,`
  line `and, —`
  line `( a ) where the return is furnished after the expiry of the time aforesaid, ending on the date of`
  line `furnishing the return; or`
  line `( b ) where no return has been furnished, ending on the date of completion of the reassessment or`
  line `recomputation under section 147 7 [or reassessment under section 153A],`
  line `on the amount by which the tax on the total income determined on the basis of such reassessment or`
  line `recomputation exceeds the tax on the total 8 [income determined under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143 or on`
  line `the basis of the earlier assessment aforesaid].`
  line `9 * * * * *`
  line `( 4 ) Where as a result of an order under section 154 or section 155 or section 250 or section`
  line `254 or section 260 or section 262 or section 263 or section 264 or an order of the Settlement Commission`
  line `under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 245D, the amount of tax on which interest was payable under sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) or sub-section ( 3 ) of this section has been increased or reduced, as the case may be, the interest shall`
  line `be increased or reduced accordingly, and —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the interest is increased, the Assessing Officer shall serve on the assessee a`
  line `notice of demand in the prescribed form specifying the sum payable, and such notice of demand shall`
  line `be deemed to be a notice under section 156 and the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly;`
  line `( ii ) in a case where the interest is reduced, the excess interest paid, if any, shall be refunded.`
  line `( 5 ) The provisions of this section shall apply in respect of assessments for the assessment year`
  line `commencing on the 1st day of April, 1989 and subsequent assessment years.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 85 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 38, for Explanation (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 89, for “under section 147” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2003).`
  line `4. Explanation omitted by Act 14 of 2001, s. 78 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 38 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 12, for “one and one - fourth per cent.” (w.e.f. 8 -9-2003).Earlier substitution by Act 27 of 1999,`
  line `s. 81 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `7. Ins. by 32 of 2003, s. 89 (w.e.f 1-6-2003).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 38, for “income determined on the basis of the earlier assessment aforesaid” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `9. The Explanation omitted by s. 38, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
