obj_root_law_sections_694_content:
  string
  line 694
  line `234B. Interest for defaults in payment of advance tax. — ( 1 ) Subject to the other provisions of this`
  line `section, where, in any financial year, an assessee who is liable to pay advance tax under section 208 has`
  line `failed to pay such tax or, where the advance tax paid by such assessee under the provisions of section`
  line `210 is less than ninety per cent. of the assessed tax, the assessee shall be liable to pay simple interest at`
  line `the rate of 1 [one per cent.] for every month or part of a month comprised in the period from the 1st day of`
  line `April next following such financial year 2 [to the date of determination of total income under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143 3 [and where a regular assessment is made, to the date of such regular`
  line `assessment, on an amount]] equal to the assessed tax or, as the case may be, on the amount by which the`
  line `advance tax paid as aforesaid falls short of the assessed tax.`
  line `4 [ Explanation 1. —In this section, “assessed tax” means the tax on the total income determined under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143 and where a regular assessment is made, the tax on the total income`
  line `determined under such regular assessment as reduced by the amount of, —`
  line `( i ) any tax deducted or collected at source in accordance with the provisions of Chapter XVII on`
  line `any income which is subject to such deduction or collection and which is taken into account in`
  line `computing such total income;`
  line `( ii ) any relief of tax allowed under section 90 on account of tax paid in a country outside India;`
  line `( iii ) any relief of tax allowed under section 90A on account of tax paid in a specified territory`
  line `outside India referred to in that section;`
  line `( iv ) any deduction, from the Indian income-tax payable, allowed under section 91, on account of`
  line `tax paid in a country outside India; and`
  line `( v ) any tax credit allowed to be set off in accordance with the provisions of section 115JAA`
  line `5 [or section 115JD].]`
  line `Explanation 2. — Where, in relation to an assessment year, an assessment is made for the first time`
  line `6 [under section 147 or section 153A], the assessment so made shall be regarded as a regular assessment`
  line `for the purposes of this section.`
  line `7 [ Explanation 3. — In Explanation 1 and in sub-section ( 3 ) “tax on the total income determined under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143” shall not include the additional income -tax, if any, payable under`
  line `section 143.]`
  line `( 2 ) Where, before the date of 8 [determination of total income under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143 or]`
  line `completion of a regular assessment, tax is paid by the assessee under section 140A or otherwise, —`
  line `( i ) interest shall be calculated in accordance with the foregoing provisions of this section up to the`
  line `date on which the tax is so paid, and reduced by the interest, if any, paid under section 140A towards`
  line `the interest chargeable under this section;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 13, for “one and one - fourth per cent.” (w.e.f. 8 -9-2003).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 39, for “to the date of the regular assessment” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 42, for “or regular assessment, on an amount” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 49, for Explanation 1 (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 86 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 90, for “under section 147” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2003).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 39, for Explanation 3 (w.e.f.1-4-1989 ).`
  line `8. Ins. by s. 39, ibid (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
