  line 695
  line `( ii ) thereafter, interest shall be calculated at the rate aforesaid on the amount by which the tax so`
  line `paid together with the advance tax paid falls short of the assessed tax.`
  line `1 [( 2A ) ( a ) where an application under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 245C for any assessment year has`
  line `been made, the assessee shall be liable to pay simple interest at the rate of one per cent. for every month`
  line `or part of a month comprised in the period commencing on the 1st day of April of such assessment year`
  line `and ending on the date of making such application, on the additional amount of income-tax referred to in`
  line `that sub-section;`
  line `( b ) where as a result of an order of the Settlement Commission under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 245D`
  line `for any assessment year, the amount of total income disclosed in the application under sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 245C is increased, the assessee shall be liable to pay simple interest at the rate of one per cent. for`
  line `every month or part of a month comprised in the period commencing on the 1st day of April of such`
  line `assessment year and ending on the date of such order, on the amount by which the tax on the total income`
  line `determined on the basis of such order exceeds the tax on the total income disclosed in the application`
  line `filed under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 245C;`
  line `( c ) where, as a result of an order under sub-section ( 6B ) of section 245D, the amount on which`
  line `interest was payable under clause ( b ) has been increased or reduced, as the case may be, the interest shall`
  line `be increased or reduced accordingly;]`
  line `2 [( 3 ) where, as a result of an order of reassessment or recomputation under section 147 or`
  line `section 153A, the amount on which interest was payable in respect of shortfall in payment of advance tax`
  line `for any financial year under sub-section ( 1 ) is increased, the assessee shall be liable to pay simple interest`
  line `at the rate of one per cent. for every month or part of a month comprised in the period commencing on the`
  line `1st day of April next following such financial year and ending on the date of the reassessment or`
  line `recomputation under section 147 or section 153A, on the amount by which the tax on the total income`
  line `determined on the basis of the reassessment or recomputation exceeds the tax on the total income`
  line `determined under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143 or on the basis of the regular assessment as referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ), as the case may be;]`
  line `( 4 ) where, as a result of an order under section 154 or section 155 or section 250 or section 254 or`
  line `section 260 or section 262 or section 263 or section 264 3 ***, the amount on which interest was payable`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 3 ) has been increased or reduced, as the case may be, the interest`
  line `shall be increased or reduced accordingly, and —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the interest is increased, the Assessing Officer shall serve on the assessee a`
  line `notice of demand in the prescribed form specifying the sum payable and such notice of demand shall`
  line `be deemed to be a notice under section 156 and the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly;`
  line `( ii ) in a case where the interest is reduced, the excess interest paid, if any, shall be refunded;`
  line `( 5 ) the provisions of this section shall apply in respect of assessments for the assessment year`
  line `commencing on the 1st day of April, 1989 and subsequent assessment years.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 57 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 57, ibid., for sub-section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line `3. The words, brackets, figures and letter “or an order of the Settlement Commission under sub - section (4) of section 245D”`
  line `omitted by s. 57, ibid (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
