obj_root_law_sections_696_content:
  string
  line 696
  line `234C. Interest for deferment of advance tax. — 1 [( 1 ) Where in any financial year, —`
  line `2 [( a ) an assessee, other than 3 [the assessee referred to in clause ( b )], who is liable to pay advance`
  line `tax under section 208 has failed to pay such tax or —`
  line `( i ) the advance tax paid by such assessee on its current income on or before the 15th day of`
  line `June is less than fifteen per cent. of the tax due on the returned income or the amount of such`
  line `advance tax paid on or before the 15th day of September is less than forty-five per cent. of the tax`
  line `due on the returned income or the amount of such advance tax paid on or before the 15th day of`
  line `December is less than seventy-five per cent. of the tax due on the returned income, then, the`
  line `assessee shall be liable to pay simple interest at the rate of one per cent. per month for a period of`
  line `three months on the amount of the shortfall from fifteen per cent or forty-five per cent. or`
  line `seventy-five per cent., as the case may be, of the tax due on the returned income;`
  line `( ii ) the advance tax paid by the assessee on the current income on or before the 15th day of`
  line `March is less than the tax due on the returned income, then, the assessee shall be liable to pay`
  line `simple interest at the rate of one per cent. on the amount of the shortfall from the tax due on the`
  line `returned income:]`
  line `Provided that if the advance tax paid by the assessee on the current income, on or before the`
  line `15th day of June or the 15th day of September, is not less than twelve per cent or, as the case may`
  line `be, thirty-six per cent. of the tax due on the returned income, then, the assessee shall not be liable`
  line `to pay any interest on the amount of the shortfall on those dates;]`
  line `( b ) 4 [ 5 [ an assessee who declares profits and gains in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 44AD or sub-section ( 1 ) of section 44ADA, as the case may be ], who is`
  line `liable to pay advance tax under section 208 has failed to pay such tax or the advance tax paid by the`
  line `assessee on its current income on or before the 15th day of March is less than the tax due on the`
  line `returned income, then, the assessee shall be liable to pay simple interest at the rate of one per cent on`
  line `the amount of the shortfall from the tax due on the returned income:]`
  line `6 [Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply to any shortfall in the payment of the`
  line `tax due on the returned income where such shortfall is on account of under-estimate or failure to`
  line `estimate —`
  line `( a ) the amount of capital gains; or`
  line `( b ) income of the nature referred to in sub-clause ( ix ) of clause ( 24 ) of 7 [section 2; or]`
  line `8 [( c ) income under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession” in cases where the`
  line `income accrues or arises under the said head for the 9 [ first time; or]]`
  line `10 [ ( d ) income of the nature referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115BBDA,]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 45, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 91, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 75, for “an eligible assessee in respect of the eligible business referred to in section 44AD”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 91, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 75, for “an eligible assessee in respect of the eligible business referred to in section 44AD”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 91, for “section 2” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2016).`
  line `8. Ins. by s. 91, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 75, for “first time,” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `10. Ins. by s. 75, ibid (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
