  line 697
  line `and the assessee has paid the whole of the amount of tax payable in respect of income referred to in`
  line `clause ( a ) 1 [or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ) 2 [or clause ( d )]], as the case may be, had such income been a part of`
  line `the total income, as part of the 3 [remaining instalments of advance tax which are due or where no such`
  line `instalments are due], by the 31st day of March of the financial year:]`
  line `4 [Provided further that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply to any shortfall in the`
  line `payment of the tax due on the returned income where such shortfall is on account of increase in the rate of`
  line `surcharge under section 2 of the Finance Act, 2000 (10 of 2000), as amended by the Taxation Laws`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2000 (1 of 2001), and the assessee has paid the amount of shortfall, on or before the`
  line `15th day of March, 2001 in respect of the instalment of advance tax due on the 15th day of June, 2000,`
  line `the 15th day of September, 2000 and the 15th day of December, 2000:]`
  line `5 [Provided also that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply to any shortfall in the payment`
  line `of the tax due on the returned income where such shortfall is on account of increase in the rate of`
  line `surcharge under section 2 of the Finance Act, 2000 (10 of 2000) as amended by the Taxation Laws`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2001 (4 of 2001) and the assessee has paid the amount of shortfall on or before the`
  line `15th day of March, 2001 in respect of the instalment of advance tax due on the 15th day of June, 2000,`
  line `the 15th day of September, 2000 and 15th day of December, 2000.]`
  line `6 [ Explanation. — In th is section, “tax due on the returned income” means the tax chargeable on the`
  line `total income declared in the return of income furnished by the assessee for the assessment year`
  line `commencing on the 1st day of April immediately following the financial year in which the advance tax is`
  line `paid or payable, as reduced by the amount of, —`
  line `( i ) any tax deductible or collectible at source in accordance with the provisions of Chapter XVII`
  line `on any income which is subject to such deduction or collection and which is taken into account in`
  line `computing such total income;`
  line `( ii ) any relief of tax allowed under section 90 on account of tax paid in a country outside India;`
  line `( iii ) any relief of tax allowed under section 90A on account of tax paid in a specified territory`
  line `outside India referred to in that section;`
  line `( iv ) any deduction, from the Indian income-tax payable, allowed under section 91, on account of`
  line `tax paid in a country outside India; and`
  line `( v ) any tax credit allowed to be set off in accordance with the provisions of section`
  line `115JAA 7 [or section 115JD].]`
  line `( 2 ) The provisions of this section shall apply in respect of assessments for the assessment year`
  line `commencing on the 1st day of April, 1989 and subsequent assessment years.]]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 91, for “or clause ( b )” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2016).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 75 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 54, for “instalment of advance tax which is immediately due or where no such instalment is so`
  line `due” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1997).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 1 of 2001, s. 4 (w.e.f. 4-1-2001).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 4 of 2001, s. 7 (w.e.f 3-2-2001).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 50, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 87 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
