obj_root_law_sections_698_content:
  string
  line 698
  line `1 [ 234D. Interest on excess refund. — ( 1 ) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, where any refund`
  line `is granted to the assessee under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143, and —`
  line `( a ) no refund is due on regular assessment; or`
  line `( b ) the amount refunded under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143 exceeds the amount refundable on`
  line `regular assessment,`
  line `the assessee shall be liable to pay simple interest at the rate of 2 [one-half per cent.] on the whole or the`
  line `excess amount so refunded, for every month or part of a month comprised in the period from the date of`
  line `grant of refund to the date of such regular assessment.`
  line `( 2 ) Where, as a result of an order under section 154 or section 155 or section 250 or section`
  line `254 or section 260 or section 262 or section 263 or section 264 or an order of the Settlement Commission`
  line `under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 245D, the amount of refund granted under sub-section ( 1 ) of section`
  line `143 is held to be correctly allowed, either in whole or in part, as the case may be, then, the interest`
  line `chargeable, if any, under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be reduced accordingly.`
  line `3 [ Explanation 1]. — Where, in relation to an assessment year, an assessment is made for the first time`
  line `under section 147 or section 153A, the assessment so made shall be regarded as a regular assessment for`
  line `the purposes of this section.]`
  line `4 [ Explanation 2. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the provisions of this section`
  line `shall also apply to an assessment year commencing before the 1st day of June, 2003 if the proceedings in`
  line `respect of such assessment year is completed after the said date.]`
  line `5 [ G. — Levy of fee in certain cases`
  line `234E. Fee for default in furnishing statements. — ( 1 ) Without prejudice to the provisions of the Act,`
  line `where a person fails to deliver or cause to be delivered a statement within the time prescribed in`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ) of section 200 or the proviso to sub-section ( 3 ) of section 206C, he shall be liable to pay,`
  line `by way of fee, a sum of two hundred rupees for every day during which the failure continues.`
  line `( 2 ) The amount of fee referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall not exceed the amount of tax deductible or`
  line `collectible, as the case may be.`
  line `( 3 ) The amount of fee referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be paid before delivering or causing to be`
  line `delivered a statement in accordance with sub-section ( 3 ) of section 200 or the proviso to sub-section ( 3 )`
  line `of section 206C.`
  line `( 4 ) The provisions of this section shall apply to a statement referred to in sub-section ( 3 ) of`
  line `section 200 or the proviso to sub-section ( 3 ) of section 206C which is to be delivered or caused to be`
  line `delivered for tax deducted at source or tax collected at source, as the case may be, on or after the 1st day`
  line `of July, 2012.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 91 (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 15, for “two - third per cent.” (w.e.f. 8 -9-2003).`
  line `3. The Explanation numbered as Explanation 1 by Act 23 of 2012, s. 88 (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 88, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 89, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
