  content obj_root_law_sections_699_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_699_footnotes
  sourcePage 699
obj_root_law_sections_699_content:
  string
  line 699
  line `1 [ 234F. Fee for default in furnishing return of income. — ( 1 ) Without prejudice to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, where a person required to furnish a return of income under section 139, fails to do so within the`
  line `time prescribed in sub-section (1) of the said section, he shall pay, by way of fee, a sum of, —`
  line `( a ) five thousand rupees, if the return is furnished on or before the 31st day of December of the`
  line `assessment year;`
  line `( b ) ten thousand rupees in any other case:`
  line `Provided that if the total income of the person does not exceed five lakh rupees, the fee payable`
  line `under this section shall not exceed one thousand rupees.`
  line `( 2 ) The provisions of this section shall apply in respect of return of income required to be furnished`
  line `for the assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 2018.]`
  line `CHAPTER XVIII`
  line `R ELIEF RESPECTING TAX ON DIVIDENDS IN CERTAIN CASES`
  line `235. Relief to shareholders in respect of agricultural income-tax attributable to`
  line `dividends. — [ Omitted by the Finance ( No. 2 ) ( Act, 32 of 1971), s. 28 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1972). Prior to its`
  line `omission, it was amended by the Taxation Laws (Amendment) (Act, 42 of 1970), s. 41 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1971)`
  line `and with retrospective effect from 1-4-1962, the Finance Act, (13 of 1966), s. 27 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1966) and the`
  line `Finance Act, 10 of 1965, s. 55 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1965). ]`
  line `236. Relief to company in respect of dividend paid out of past taxed profits. — ( 1 ) Where`
  line `in respect of any previous year relevant to the assessment year commencing after the 31st day of`
  line `March, 1960, an Indian company or a company which has made the prescribed arrangements for the`
  line `declaration and payment of dividends within India, pays any dividend wholly or partly out of its profits`
  line `and gains actually charged to income-tax for any assessment year ending before the 1st day of April,`
  line `1960, and deducts tax therefrom in accordance with the provisions of Chapter XVIIB, credit shall be`
  line `given to the company against the income-tax, if any, payable by it on the profits and gains of the previous`
  line `year during which the dividend is paid, of a sum calculated in accordance with the provisions of sub-`
  line `section ( 2 ), and, where the amount of credit so calculated exceeds the income-tax payable by the`
  line `company as aforesaid, the excess shall be refunded.`
  line `( 2 ) The amount of income-tax to be given as credit under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be a sum equal to ten`
  line `per cent of so much of the dividends referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) as are paid out of the profits and gains`
  line `actually charged to income-tax for any assessment year ending before the 1st day of April, 1960.`
  line `Explanation 1. — For the purposes of this section, the aggregate of the dividends declared by a`
  line `company in respect of any previous year shall be deemed first to have come out of the distributable`
  line `income of that previous year and the balance, if any, out of the undistributed part of the distributable`
  line `income of one or more previous years immediately preceding that previous year as would be just`
  line `sufficient to cover the amount of such balance and as has not likewise been taken into account for`
  line `covering such balance of any other previous year.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 76 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
