obj_root_law_sections_701_content:
  string
  line 701
  line `Explanation. — In sub-section ( 2 ) of this section and in section 280ZB, the expression “the relevant`
  line `amount of distributions of dividends” has the meaning assigned to it in the Finance Act of the relevant`
  line year.]]
  line `CHAPTER XIX`
  line REFUNDS
  line `237. Refunds. — If any person satisfies the 1 [AssessingOfficer] that the amount of tax paid by him or`
  line `on his behalf or treated as paid by him or on his behalf for any assessment year exceeds the amount with`
  line `which he is properly chargeable under this Act for that year, he shall be entitled to a refund of the excess.`
  line `238. Person entitled to claim refund in certain special cases. — ( 1 ) Where the income of one person`
  line `is included under any provision of this Act in the total income of any other person, the latter alone shall`
  line `be entitled to a refund under this Chapter in respect of such income.`
  line `2 [( 1A ) Where the value of fringe benefits provided or deemed to have been provided by one employer`
  line `is included under any provisions of Chapter XII-H in the value of fringe benefits provided or deemed to`
  line `have been provided by any other employer, the latter alone shall be entitled to a refund under this Chapter`
  line `in respect of such fringe benefits.]`
  line `( 2 ) Where through death, incapacity, insolvency, liquidation or other cause, a person is unable to`
  line `claim or receive any refund due to him, his legal representative or the trustee or guardian or receiver, as`
  line `the case may be, shall be entitled to claim or receive such refund for the benefit of such person or his`
  line estate.
  line `239. Formof claim for refund and limitation. — ( 1 ) Every claim for refund under this Chapter shall`
  line `be made in the prescribed form and verified in the prescribed manner.`
  line `3 [( 2 ) No such claim shall be allowed, unless it is made within the period specified hereunder,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( a ) where the claim is in respect of income which is assessable for any assessment year`
  line `commencing on or before the 1st day of April, 1967, four years from the last day of such assessment`
  line year;
  line `( b ) where the claim is in respect of income which is assessable for the assessment year`
  line `commencing on the first day of April, 1968, three years from the last day of the assessment year;`
  line `( c ) where the claim is in respect of income which is assessable for any other assessment year,`
  line `4 [one year] from the last day of such assessment year;]`
  line `5 [( d ) where the claim is in respect of fringe benefits which are assessable for any assessment year`
  line `commencing on or after the first day of April, 2006, one year from the last day of such`
  line `assessment year.]`
  line `240. Refund on appeal, etc. — Where, as a result of any order passed in appeal or other proceeding`
  line `under this Act, refund of any amount becomes due to the assessee, the 1 [AssessingOfficer] shall, except as`
  line `otherwise provided in this Act, refund the amount to the assessee without his having to make any claim in`
  line `that behalf:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 54, (w.e.f.1-4-2006).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 19 of 1968, s. 18, for sub-section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1968).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 82, for “two years” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1993).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 55 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
