  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_702_footnotes
  sourcePage 702
obj_root_law_sections_702_content:
  string
  line 702
  line `1 [Provided that where, by the order aforesaid, —`
  line `( a ) an assessment is set aside or cancelled and an order of fresh assessment is directed to be`
  line `made, the refund, if any, shall become due only on the making of such fresh assessment;`
  line `( b ) the assessment is annulled, the refund shall become due only of the amount, if any, of the tax`
  line `paid in excess of the tax chargeable on the total income returned by the assessee.]`
  line `241. [ Power to withhold refund in certain cases. ] — Omitted by the Finance Act, 14 of 2001, s. 81`
  line `( w.e.f. 1-6-2001).`
  line `2 [ 241A. Withholding of refund in certain cases. — For every assessment year commencing on or`
  line `after the 1st day of April, 2017, where refund of any amount becomes due to the assessee under the`
  line `provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143 and the Assessing Officer is of the opinion, having regard to`
  line `the fact that a notice has been issued under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 143 in respect of such return, that`
  line `the grant of the refund is likely to adversely affect the revenue, he may, for reasons to be recorded in`
  line `writing and with the previous approval of the Principal Commissioner or Commissioner, as the case may`
  line `be, withhold the refund up to the date on which the assessment is made. ]`
  line `242. Correctness of assessment not to be questioned. — In a claim under this Chapter, it shall not`
  line `be open to the assessee to question the correctness of any assessment or other matter decided which has`
  line `become final and conclusive or ask for a review of the same, and the assessee shall not be entitled to any`
  line `relief on such claim except refund of tax wrongly paid or paid in excess.`
  line `243. Interest on delayed refunds. — 3 [( 1 ) If the 4 [Assessing Officer] does not grant the`
  line `refund, —`
  line `( a ) in any case where the total income of the assessee does not consist solely of income from`
  line `interest on securities or dividends, within three months from the end of the month in which the total`
  line `income is determined under this Act, and`
  line `( b ) in any other case, within three months from the end of the month in which the claim for`
  line `refund is made under this Chapter,`
  line `the Central Government shall pay the assessee simple interest at 5 [fifteen per cent.] per annum on the`
  line `amount directed to be refunded from the date immediately following the expiry of the period of three`
  line `months aforesaid to the date of the order granting the refund.`
  line `Explanation. — If the delay in granting the refund within the period of three months aforesaid is`
  line `attributable to the assessee, whether wholly or in part, the period of the delay attributable to him shall be`
  line `excluded from the period for which interest is payable.]`
  line `( 2 ) Where any question arises as to the period to be excluded for the purposes of calculation of`
  line `interest under the provisions of this section, such question shall be determined by the 6 [ 7 [Principal Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 8 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] whose decision`
  line `shall be final.`
  line `9 [( 3 ) The provisions of this section shall not apply in respect of any assessment for the assessment`
  line `year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1989 or any subsequent assessment years.]`
  line `1. The proviso added by Act 4 of 1988, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 77 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 42, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 24, for “twelve per cent.” (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4 for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 96, (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_702_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_703:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-703
  sectionNo (703)
  orderNo 703
  title `Page 703`
  content obj_root_law_sections_703_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_703_footnotes
  sourcePage 703
obj_root_law_sections_703_content:
  string
  line 703
  line `244. Interest on refund where no claim is needed. — ( 1 ) Where a refund is due to the assessee in`
  line `pursuance of an order referred to in section 240 and the 1 [Assessing Officer] does not grant the refund`
  line `2 [within a period of three months from the end of the month in which such order is passed], the Central`
  line `Government shall pay to the assessee simple interest at 3 [fifteen per cent.] per annum on the amount of`
  line `refund due from the date immediately following the expiry of 4 [the period of three months aforesaid] to`
  line `the date on which the refund is granted.`
  line `5 [( 1A ) Where the whole or any part of the refund referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) is due to the assessee,`
  line `as a result of any amount having been paid by him after the 31st day of March, 1975, in pursuance of any`
  line `order of assessment or penalty and such amount or any part thereof having been found in appeal or other`
  line `proceeding under this Act to be in excess of the amount which such assessee is liable to pay as tax or`
  line `penalty, as the case may be, under this Act, the Central Government shall pay to such assessee simple`
  line `interest at the rate specified in sub-section ( 1 ) on the amount so found to be in excess from the date on`
  line `which such amount was paid to the date on which the refund is granted:`
  line `Provided that where the amount so found to be in excess was paid in instalments, such interest shall`
  line `be payable on the amount of each such instalment or any part of such instalment, which was in excess,`
  line `from the date on which such instalment was paid to the date on which the refund is granted:`
  line `Provided further that no interest under this sub-section shall be payable for a period of one month`
  line `from the date of the passing of the order in appeal or other proceeding:`
  line `Provided also that where any interest is payable to an assessee under this sub-section, no interest`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be payable to him in respect of the amount so found to be in excess.]`
  line `6 [( 1B ) Where refund of any amount becomes due to the deductor in respect of any amount paid to the`
  line `credit of the Central Government under Chapter XVIIB, such deductor shall be entitled to receive, in`
  line `addition to the said amount, simple interest thereon calculated at the rate of one-half per cent. for every`
  line `month or part of a month comprised in the period, from the date on which ––`
  line `( a ) claim for refund is made in the prescribed form; or`
  line `( b ) tax is paid, where refund arises on account of giving effect to an order under section 250 or`
  line `section 254 or section 260 or section 262,`
  line `to the date on which the refund is granted.]`
  line `( 2 ) Where a refund is withheld under the provisions of section 241, the Central Government shall pay`
  line `interest at the aforesaid rate on the amount of refund ultimately determined to be due as a result of the`
  line `appeal or further proceeding for the period commencing after the expiry of 7 [three months from the end of`
  line `the month in which the order referred to in section 241 is passed] to the date the refund is granted.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 43, for “six months from the date of such order” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1971).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 24, for “twelve per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1984).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 43, for “the period of six moths aforesaid” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1971).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 56 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 78 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 43, f or “six months from the date of the order referred to in section 241” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_703_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_704:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-704
  sectionNo (704)
  orderNo 704
  title `Page 704`
  content obj_root_law_sections_704_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_704_footnotes
  sourcePage 704
obj_root_law_sections_704_content:
  string
  line 704
  line `1 [( 3 ) The provisions of this section shall not apply in respect of any assessment for the assessment`
  line `year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1989, or any subsequent assessment years.]`
  line `2 [ 244A. Interest on refunds. — ( 1 ) 3 [Where refund of any amount becomes due to the assessee under`
  line `this Act], he shall, subject to the provisions of this section, be entitled to receive, in addition to the said`
  line `amount, simple interest thereon calculated in the following manner, namely: —`
  line `4 [( a ) where the refund is out of any tax collected at source under section 206C or paid by way of`
  line `advance tax or treated as paid under section 199, during the financial year immediately preceding the`
  line `assessment year, such interest shall be calculated at the rate of one-half per cent for every month or`
  line `part of a month comprised in the period, —`
  line `( i ) from the 1st day of April of the assessment year to the date on which the refund is granted,`
  line `if the return of income has been furnished on or before the due date specified under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139; or`
  line `( ii ) from the date of furnishing of return of income to the date on which the refund is granted,`
  line `in a case not covered under sub-clause ( i );`
  line `( aa ) where the refund is out of any tax paid under section 140A, such interest shall be calculated`
  line `at the rate of 5 [one-half per cent.] for every month or part of a month comprised in the period, from`
  line `the date of furnishing of return of income or payment of tax, whichever is later, to the date on which`
  line `the refund is granted:`
  line `Provided that no interest under clause ( a ) or clause ( aa ) shall be payable, if the amount of refund`
  line `is less than ten per cent of the tax as determined under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143 or on regular`
  line assessment;]
  line `( b ) in any other case, such interest shall be calculated at the rate of 5 [one-half per cent.] for every`
  line `month or part of a month comprised in the period or periods from the date or, as the case may be,`
  line `dates of payment of the tax or penalty to the date on which the refund is granted.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, “date of payment of tax or penalty” means the dat e on`
  line `and from which the amount of tax or penalty specified in the notice of demand issued under section 156 is`
  line `paid in excess of such demand.`
  line `6 [( 1A ) In a case where a refund arises as a result of giving effect to an order under section`
  line `250 or section 254 or section 260 or section 262 or section 263 or section 264, wholly or partly, otherwise`
  line `than by making a fresh assessment or reassessment, the assessee shall be entitled to receive, in addition to`
  line `the interest payable under sub-section ( 1 ), an additional interest on such amount of refund calculated at`
  line `the rate of three per cent per annum, for the period beginning from the date following the date of expiry of`
  line `the time allowed under sub-section ( 5 ) ofsection 153 to the date on which the refund is granted.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 97 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 98, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 41, for “Where, in pursuance of any order p assed under this Act, refund of any amount`
  line `becomes due to the assessee” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 92, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 16, for “two - third per cent.” (w.e.f. 8 -9-2003).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 92 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
