  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_705_footnotes
  sourcePage 705
obj_root_law_sections_705_content:
  string
  line 705
  line `1 [( 1B ) Where refund of anyamount becomes due to the deductor in respect of any amount paid to the`
  line `credit of the Central Government under Chapter XVII-B, such deductor shall be entitled to receive, in`
  line `addition to the said amount, simple interest thereon calculated at the rate of one-half per cent for every`
  line `month or part of a month comprised in the period, from the date on which —`
  line `( a ) claim for refund is made in the prescribed form; or`
  line `( b ) tax is paid, where refundarises on account of giving effect to an order under section`
  line `250 or section 254 or section 260 or section 262,`
  line `to the date on which the refund is granted. ]`
  line `( 2 ) If the proceedings resulting in the refund are delayed for reasons attributable to the assessee 1 [ or`
  line `the deductor, as the case may be, ] whether wholly or in part, the period of the delay so attributable to him`
  line `shall be excluded from the period for which interest is payable 2 [under sub-section ( 1 ) or ( 1A )] 1 [or ( 1B )],`
  line `and where any question arises as to the period to be excluded, it shall be decided by the 3 [Principal Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] whose decision`
  line `thereon shall be final.`
  line `( 3 ) Where, as a 5 [result of an order under sub-section ( 3 ) of section 115WE or`
  line `section 115WF or section 115WG or] 6 [sub-section ( 3 ) of section 143 or section 144 or] section 147 or`
  line `section 154 or section 155 or section 250 or section 254 or section 260 or section 262 or section`
  line `263 or section 264 or an order of the Settlement Commission under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 245D, the`
  line `amount on which interest was payable under sub-section ( 1 ) has been increased or reduced, as the case`
  line `may be, the interest shall be increased or reduced accordingly, and in a case where the interest is reduced,`
  line `the Assessing Officer shall serve on the assessee a notice of demand in the prescribed form specifying the`
  line `amount of the excess interest paid and requiring him to pay such amount; and such notice of demand shall`
  line `be deemed to be a notice under section 156 and the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly.`
  line `( 4 ) The provisions of this section shall apply in respect of assessments for the assessment year`
  line `commencing on the 1st day of April, 1989, and subsequent assessment years:]`
  line `7 [Provided that in respect of assessment of fringe benefits, the provisions of this sub-section shall`
  line `have effect as if for the figures “1989”, the figures “2006” had been substituted.]`
  line `245. Set off of refunds against tax remaining payable. — Where under any of the provisions of this`
  line `Act, a refund is found to be due to any person, the 8 [Assessing Officer], 9 [Deputy Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals)] 10 [, or the Commissioner (Appeals) or Commissioner or 11 [ 3 [Principal Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Chief Commissioner] or 4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]]], as the case may be, may, in lieu`
  line `of payment of the refund, set off the amount to be refunded or any part of that amount, against the sum, if`
  line `any, remaining payable under this Act by the person to whom the refund is due, after giving an intimation`
  line `in writing to such person of the action proposed to be taken under this section.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 78 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 92 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 56, for “result of an order” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 41(w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `7. The proviso ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 56 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `9. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
