obj_root_law_sections_706_content:
  string
  line 706
  line `1 [CHAPTER XIXA`
  line `S ETTLEMENTOF C ASES`
  line `2 [ 245A. Definitions. — In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “Bench” means a Bench of the Settlement Commission;`
  line `3 [( b ) “case” means any proceeding for assessment under this Act, of any person in respect of any`
  line `assessment year or assessment years which may be pending before an Assessing Officer on the date`
  line `on which an application under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 245C is made.`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause —`
  line `5 [( i ) a proceeding for assessment or reassessment or recomputation under section 147 shall be`
  line `deemed to have commenced —`
  line `( a ) from the date on which a notice under section 148 is issued for any assessment year;`
  line `( b ) from the date of issuance of the notice referred to in sub-clause ( a ), for any other`
  line `assessment year or assessment years for which a notice under section 148 has not been issued, but`
  line `such notice could have been issued on such date, if the return of income for the other assessment`
  line `year or assessment years has been furnished under section 139 or in response to a notice`
  line `under section 142;]`
  line `6 * * * * *`
  line `7 [( iii ) a proceeding for making fresh assessment in pursuance of an order under`
  line `section 254 or section 263 or section 264, setting aside or cancelling an assessment shall be deemed`
  line `to have commenced from the date on which such order, setting aside or cancelling an assessment was`
  line passed;]
  line `8 [( iiia ) a proceeding for assessment or reassessment for any of the assessment years, referred to in`
  line `clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 153A in case of a person referred to in section 153Aor`
  line `section 153C, shall be deemed to have commenced on the date of issue of notice initiating such`
  line `proceeding and concluded on the date on which the assessment is made;]`
  line `( iv ) a proceeding for assessment for any assessment year, other than the proceedings of`
  line `assessment or reassessment referred to in 9 [clause ( i ) or clause ( iii ) or clause ( iiia ) ], shall be deemed`
  line `to have commenced 10 [from the date on which the return of income for that assessment year is`
  line `furnished under section 139 or in response to a notice served under section 142 and concluded on the`
  line `date on which the assessment is made; or on the expiry of 11 [ the time specified for making assessment`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 153], in case where no assessment is made];]`
  line `( c ) “Chairman” means the Chairman o f the Settlement Commission;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 57 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 57, for section 245A (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 62, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `4. The proviso omitted by Act 25 of 2014, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 58, for clause ( i ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line `6. Clause ( ii ) omitted by Act 14 of 2010, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1-6-2010).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 65, for clause ( iii ) (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1-6-2010).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 65, for “clause ( i ) or clause ( iv ) of the proviso or clause ( iiia ) of the Explanation ”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 58, for “from the 1st day of the assessment year and concluded on the date on which the`
  line `assessment is made” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2015).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 79, for “two years from the end of the relevant assessment year” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
