obj_root_law_sections_707_content:
  string
  line 707
  line `( d ) “income -tax authority ” means an income -tax authority specified in section 116;`
  line `( e ) “Member” means a Member of the Settlement Commission, and includes the Chairman and a`
  line Vice-Chairman;
  line `( f ) “Settlement Commission” means the Income-tax Settlement Commission constituted`
  line `under section 245B;`
  line `( g ) “Vice - Chairman” means a Vice -Chairman of the Settlement Commission 1 [and includes a`
  line `Member who is senior amongst the Members of a Bench].]`
  line `245B. Income-tax Settlement Commission. — ( 1 ) The Central Government shall constitute a`
  line `Commission to be called the Income-tax Settlement Commission 2 *** for the settlement of cases under`
  line `this Chapter.`
  line `( 2 ) The Settlement Commission shall consist of a Chairman 3 [and as many Vice-Chairmen and other`
  line `members as the Central Government thinks fit] and shall function within the Department of the Central`
  line `Government dealing with direct taxes.`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `( 3 ) The Chairman 5 [, Vice-Chairman] and other members of the Settlement Commission shall be`
  line `appointed by the Central Government from amongst persons of integrity and outstanding ability, having`
  line `special knowledge of, and, experience in, problems relating to direct taxes and business accounts:`
  line `Provided that, where a member of the Board is appointed as the Chairman 5 [, Vice-Chairman] or as a`
  line `member of the Settlement Commission, he shall cease to be a member of the Board.`
  line `6 * * * * *`
  line `7 [ 245BA. Jurisdiction and powers of Settlement Commission. — ( 1 ) Subject to the other provisions`
  line `of this Chapter, the jurisdiction, powers and authority of the Settlement Commission may be exercised by`
  line `Benches thereof.`
  line `( 2 ) Subject to the other provisions of this section, a Bench shall be presided over by the Chairman or`
  line `a Vice-Chairman and shall consist of two other Members.`
  line `( 3 ) The Bench for which the Chairman is the Presiding Officer shall be the principal Bench and the`
  line `other Benches shall be known as additional Benches.`
  line `( 4 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ), the Chairman may authorise the`
  line `Vice-Chairman or other Member appointed to one Bench to discharge also the functions of the`
  line `Vice-Chairman or, as the case may be, other Member of another Bench.`
  line `( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, and subject to any`
  line `rules that may be made in this behalf, when one of the persons constituting a Bench (whether such person`
  line `be the Presiding Officer or other Member of the Bench) is unable to discharge his functions owing to`
  line `absence, illness or any other cause or in the event of the occurrence of any vacancy either in the office of`
  line `the Presiding Officer or in the office of one or the other Members of the Bench, the remaining two`
  line `persons may function as the Bench and if the Presiding Officer of the Bench is not one of the remaining`
  line `two persons, the senior among the remaining persons shall act as the Presiding Officer of the Bench:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 62 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `2. The brac kets and words ‘(hereafter in this Chapter referred to as “the Settlement Commission”)’ omitted by Act 11 of`
  line `1987, s. 58 (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 15, for “and two other members” (w.e.f. 10 -9-1986).`
  line `4. Sub-section ( 2A ) omitted by s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 15, ibid (w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
  line `6. The second proviso omitted by s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 59 (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_707_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_708:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-708
  sectionNo (708)
  orderNo 708
  title `Page 708`
  content obj_root_law_sections_708_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_708_footnotes
  sourcePage 708
obj_root_law_sections_708_content:
  string
  line 708
  line `Provided that if at any stage of the hearing of any such case or matter, it appears to the Presiding`
  line `Officer that the case or matter is of such a nature that it ought to be heard of by a Bench consisting of`
  line `three Members, the case or matter may be referred by the Presiding Officer of such Bench to the`
  line `Chairman for transfer to such Bench as the Chairman may deem fit.`
  line `1 [( 5A ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, the Chairman`
  line `may, for the disposal of any particular case, constitute a Special Bench consisting of more than three`
  line Members.]
  line `( 6 ) Subject to the other provisions of this Chapter, the places at which the principal Bench and the`
  line `additional Benches shall ordinarily sit shall be such as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, specify 1 [and the Special Bench shall sit at a place to be fixed by the Chairman].]`
  line `2 [ 245BB. Vice-Chairman to act as Chairman or to discharge his functions in certain`
  line `circumstances. — ( 1 ) In the event of the occurrence of any vacancy in the office of the Chairman by`
  line `reason of his death, resignation or otherwise, the Vice-Chairman or, as the case may be, such one of the`
  line `Vice-Chairmen as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, authorise in this`
  line `behalf, shall act as the Chairman until the date on which a new Chairman, appointed in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of this Chapter to fill such vacancy, enters upon his office.`
  line `( 2 ) When the Chairman is unable to discharge his functions owing to absence, illness or any other`
  line `cause, the Vice-Chairman or, as the case may be, such one of the Vice-Chairmen as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, authorise in this behalf, shall discharge the`
  line `functions of the Chairman until the date on which the Chairman resumes his duties.]`
  line `2 [ 245BC. Power of Chairman to transfer cases from one Bench to another. — On the application`
  line `of the assessee or the 3 [ 4 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 5 [Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner]]and after notice to them, and after hearing such of them as he may`
  line `desire to be heard, or on his own motion without such notice, the Chairman may transfer any case`
  line `pending before one Bench, for disposal, to another Bench. ]`
  line `2 [ 245BD. Decision to be by majority. — If the Members of a Bench differ in opinion on any point,`
  line `the point shall be decided according to the opinion of the majority, if there is a majority, but if the`
  line `Members are equally divided, they shall state the point or points on which they differ, and make a`
  line `reference to the Chairman who shall either hear the point or points himself or refer the case for hearing on`
  line `such point or points by one or more of the other Members of the Settlement Commission and such point`
  line `or points shall be decided according to the opinion of the majority of the Members of the Settlement`
  line `Commission who have heard the case, including those who first heard it.]`
  line `245C. Application for settlement of cases. — 6 [( 1 ) An assessee may, at any stage of a case relating to`
  line `him, make an application in such form and in such manner as may be prescribed, and containing a full`
  line `and true disclosure of his income which has not been disclosed before the 7 [Assessing Officer], the`
  line `manner in which such income has been derived, the additional amount of income-tax payable on such`
  line `income and such other particulars as may be prescribed, to the Settlement Commission to have the case`
  line `settled and any such application shall be disposed of in the manner hereinafter provided:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 59 (w.e.f. 1-6-1987)`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4 for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 40 for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income tax” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_708_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_709:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-709
  sectionNo (709)
  orderNo 709
  title `Page 709`
  content obj_root_law_sections_709_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_709_footnotes
  sourcePage 709
obj_root_law_sections_709_content:
  string
  line 709
  line `1 [Provided that no such application shall be made unless, —`
  line `( i ) in a case where proceedings for assessment or reassessment for any of the assessment years`
  line `referred to in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 153A or clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section`
  line `153B in case of a person referred to in section 153A or section 153C have been initiated, the`
  line `additional amount of income-tax payable on the income disclosed in the application exceeds`
  line `fifty lakh rupees,`
  line `2 [( ia ) in a case where —`
  line `( A ) the applicant is related to the person referred to in clause ( i ) who has filed an application`
  line `(hereafter in this sub- section referred to as “specified person”); and`
  line `( B ) the proceedings for assessment or re-assessment for any of the assessment years referred`
  line `to in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 153A or clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 153B in case of the applicant, being a person referred to in section 153A or section 153C,`
  line `have been initiated,`
  line `the additional amount of income-tax payable on the income disclosed in the application exceeds`
  line `ten lakh rupees,]`
  line `( ii ) in any other case, the additional amount of income-tax payable on the income disclosed in the`
  line `application exceeds ten lakh rupees,`
  line `and such tax and the interest thereon, which would have been paid under the provisions of this Act had`
  line `the income disclosed in the application been declared in the return of income before the Assessing Officer`
  line `on the date of application, has been paid on or before the date of making the application and the proof of`
  line `such payment is attached with the application.]`
  line `2 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of clause ( ia ), —`
  line `( a ) the applicant, in relation to the specified person referred to in clause ( ia ), means, —`
  line `( i ) where the specified person is an individual, any relative of the specified person;`
  line `( ii ) where the specified person is a company, firm, association of persons or Hindu undivided`
  line `family, any director of the company, partner of the firm, or member of the association or family,`
  line `or any relative of such director, partner or member;`
  line `( iii ) any individual who has a substantial interest in the business or profession of the specified`
  line `person, or any relative of such individual;`
  line `( iv ) a company, firm, association of persons or Hindu undivided family having a substantial`
  line `interest in the business or profession of the specified person or any director, partner or member of`
  line `such company, firm, association or family, or any relative of such director, partner or member;`
  line `( v ) a company, firm, association of persons or Hindu undivided family of which a director,`
  line `partner or member, as the case may be, has a substantial interest in the business or profession of`
  line `the specified person; or any director, partner or member of such company, firm, association or`
  line `family or any relative of such director, partner or member;`
  line `( vi ) any person who carries on a business or profession, —`
  line `( A ) where the specified person being an individual, or any relative of such specified`
  line `person, has a substantial interest in the business or profession of that person; or`
  line `( B ) where the specified person being a company, firm, association of persons or Hindu`
  line `undivided family, or any director of such company, partner of such firm or member of the`
  line `association or family, or any relative of such director, partner or member, has a substantial`
  line `interest in the business or profession of that person;`
  line `1. The proviso subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 46, (w.e.f. 1-6-2010).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 29, (w.e.f. 1-6-2011).`
obj_root_law_sections_709_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_710:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-710
  sectionNo (710)
  orderNo 710
  title `Page 710`
  content obj_root_law_sections_710_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_710_footnotes
  sourcePage 710
obj_root_law_sections_710_content:
  string
  line 710
  line `( b ) a person shall be deemed to have a substantial interest in a business or profession, if —`
  line `( A ) in a case where the business or profession is carried on by a company, such person is,`
  line `1 [on the date of search], the beneficial owner of shares (not being shares entitled to a fixed rate of`
  line `dividend, whether with or without a right to participate in profits) carrying not less than twenty`
  line `per cent of the voting power; and`
  line `( B ) in any other case, such person is, 1 [on the date of search], beneficially entitled to not less`
  line `than twenty per cent of the profits of such business or profession.]`
  line `( 1A ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ) of this section 2 ***, the additional amount of income-tax`
  line `payable in respect of the income disclosed in an application made under sub-section ( 1 ) of this section`
  line `shall be the amount calculated in accordance with the provisions of sub-sections ( 1B ) to ( 1D ).`
  line `3 [( 1B ) Where the income disclosed in the application relates to only one previous year, —`
  line `( i ) if the applicant has not furnished a return in respect of the total income of that year, then, tax`
  line `shall be calculated on the income disclosed in the application as if such income were the total income;`
  line `( ii ) if the applicant has furnished a return in respect of the total income of that year, tax shall be`
  line `calculated on the aggregate of the total income returned and the income disclosed in the application as`
  line `if such aggregate were the total income.]`
  line `4 [( 1C ) The additional amount of income-tax payable in respect of the income disclosed in the`
  line `application relating to the previous year referred to in sub-section ( 1B ) shall be, —`
  line `( a ) in a case referred to in clause ( i ) of that sub-section, the amount of tax calculated under that`
  line clause;
  line `( b ) in a case referred to in clause ( ii ) of that sub-section, the amount of tax calculated under that`
  line `clause as reduced by the amount of tax calculated on the total income returned for that year;`
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `( 1D ) Where the income disclosed in the application relates to more than one previous year, the`
  line `additional amount of income-tax payable in respect of the income disclosed for each of the years shall`
  line `first be calculated in accordance with the provisions of sub-sections ( 1B ) and ( 1C ) and the aggregate of`
  line `the amount so arrived at in respect of each of the years for which the application has been made under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) shall be the additional amount of income-tax payable in respect of the income disclosed in`
  line `the application.`
  line `6 * * * * *`
  line `( 2 ) Every application made under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be accompanied by such fees as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line `( 3 ) An application made under sub-section ( 1 ) shall not be allowed to be withdrawn by the applicant.`
  line `7 [( 4 ) An assessee shall, on the date on which he makes an application under sub-section ( 1 ) to the`
  line `Settlement Commission, also intimate the Assessing Officer in the prescribed manner of having made`
  line `such application to the said Commission.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 90, for “at any time during the previous year” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
  line `2. The words, brackets, figures and letters “and sub -sections ( 2A ) to ( 2D ) of section 245D” omitted by Act 22 of 2007, s. 63`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 60 for sub-sections ( IB ) or ( IC ) (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `4. Subs. by 22 of 2007, s. 63, for sub-section ( IB ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2007). Earlier it was substituted by Act 11 of 1987, s. 60`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `5. Clause ( c ) omitted by Act 22 of 2007, s. 63 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `6. Sub-section ( 1E ) omitted by Act 94 of 2002, s. 94 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 63 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_710_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_711:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-711
  sectionNo (711)
  orderNo 711
  title `Page 711`
  content obj_root_law_sections_711_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_711_footnotes
  sourcePage 711
obj_root_law_sections_711_content:
  string
  line 711
  line `245D. Procedure on receipt of an application under section 245C. — 1 [( 1 ) On receipt of an`
  line `application under section 245C, the Settlement Commission shall, within seven days from the date of`
  line `receipt of the application, issue a notice to the applicant requiring him to explain as to why the application`
  line `made by him be allowed to be proceeded with, and on hearing the applicant, the Settlement Commission`
  line `shall, within a period of fourteen days from the date of the application, by an order in writing, reject the`
  line `application or allow the application to be proceeded with:`
  line `Provided that where no order has been passed within the aforesaid period by the Settlement`
  line `Commission, the application shall be deemed to have been allowed to be proceeded with.]`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `( 2 ) A copy of every order under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be sent to the applicant and to the 3 [Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner].`
  line `4 [( 2A ) Where an application was made under section 245C before the 1st day of June, 2007, but an`
  line `order under the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) of this section, as they stood immediately before their`
  line `amendment by the Finance Act, 2007, has not been made before the 1st day of June, 2007, such`
  line `application shall be deemed to have been allowed to be proceeded with if the additional tax on the income`
  line `disclosed in such application and the interest thereon is paid on or before the 31st day of July, 2007.`
  line `Explanation. — In respect of the applications referred to in this sub-section, the 31st day of July, 2007`
  line `shall be deemed to be the date of the order of rejection or allowing the application to be proceeded with`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 2B ) The Settlement Commission shall, —`
  line `( i ) in respect of an application which is allowed to be proceeded with under sub-section ( 1 ),`
  line `within thirty days from the date on which the application was made; or`
  line `( ii ) in respect of an application referred to in sub-section ( 2A ) which is deemed to have been`
  line `allowed to be proceeded with under that sub-section, on or before the 7th day of August, 2007,`
  line `call for a report from the 3 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner], and the 3 [Principal Commissioner`
  line `or Commissioner] shall furnish the report within a period of thirty days of the receipt of communication`
  line `from the Settlement Commission.`
  line `( 2C ) Where a report of the 3 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] called for under`
  line `sub-section ( 2B ) has been furnished within the period specified therein, the Settlement Commission may,`
  line `on the basis of the report and within a period of fifteen days of the receipt of the report, by an order in`
  line `writing, declare the application in question as invalid, and shall send the copy of such order to the`
  line `applicant and the 3 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 64, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `2. Sub-section ( 1A ) omitted by Act 49 of 1991, s. 66 (w.e.f. 27-9-1991).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 64, for sub-sections ( 2A ), ( 2B ), ( 2C ) and ( 2D ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_711_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_712:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-712
  sectionNo (712)
  orderNo 712
  title `Page 712`
  content obj_root_law_sections_712_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_712_footnotes
  sourcePage 712
obj_root_law_sections_712_content:
  string
  line 712
  line `Provided that an application shall not be declared invalid unless an opportunity has been given to the`
  line `applicant of being heard:`
  line `Provided further that where the 1 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] has not furnished the`
  line `report within the aforesaid period, the Settlement Commission shall proceed further in the matter without`
  line `the report of the 1 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner].`
  line `( 2D ) Where an application was made under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 245C before the 1st day of`
  line `June, 2007 and an order under the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) of this section, as they stood immediately`
  line `before their amendment by the Finance Act, 2007, allowing the application to have been proceeded with,`
  line `has been passed before the 1st day of June, 2007, but an order under the provisions of sub-section ( 4 ), as`
  line `they stood immediately before their amendment by the Finance Act, 2007, was not passed before the 1st`
  line `day of June, 2007, such application shall not be allowed to be further proceeded with unless the additional`
  line `tax on the income disclosed in such application and the interest thereon, is, notwithstanding any extension`
  line `of time already granted by the Settlement Commission, paid on or before the 31st day of July, 2007.]`
  line `2 [( 3 ) The Settlement Commission, in respect of —`
  line `( i ) an application which has not been declared invalid under sub-section ( 2C ); or`
  line `( ii ) an application referred to in sub-section ( 2D ) which has been allowed to be further proceeded`
  line `with under that sub-section,`
  line `may call for the records from the 1 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] and after examination of`
  line `such records, if the Settlement Commission is of the opinion that any further enquiry or investigation in`
  line `the matter is necessary, it may direct the 1 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] to make or cause to`
  line `be made such further enquiry or investigation and furnish a report on the matters covered by the`
  line `application and any other matter relating to the case, and the 1 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]`
  line `shall furnish the report within a period of ninety days of the receipt of communication from the`
  line `Settlement Commission:`
  line `Provided that where the 1 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] does not furnish the report`
  line `within the aforesaid period, the Settlement Commission may proceed to pass an order under`
  line `sub-section ( 4 ) without such report.`
  line `( 4 ) After examination of the records and the report of the 1 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner], if any, received under —`
  line `( i ) sub-section ( 2B ) or sub-section ( 3 ), or`
  line `( ii ) the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) as they stood immediately before their amendment by the`
  line `Finance Act, 2007,`
  line `and after giving an opportunity to the applicant and to the 1 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] to`
  line `be heard, either in person or through a representative duly authorised in this behalf, and after examining`
  line `such further evidence as may be placed before it or obtained by it, the Settlement Commission may, in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act, pass such order as it thinks fit on the matters covered by the`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 64, for sub-sections ( 3 ), ( 4 ) and ( 4A ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_712_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_713:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-713
  sectionNo (713)
  orderNo 713
  title `Page 713`
  content obj_root_law_sections_713_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_713_footnotes
  sourcePage 713
obj_root_law_sections_713_content:
  string
  line 713
  line `application and any other matter relating to the case not covered by the application, but referred to in the`
  line `report of the 1 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner].`
  line `( 4A ) The Settlement Commission shall pass an order under sub-section ( 4 ), —`
  line `( i ) in respect of an application referred to in sub-section ( 2A ) or sub-section ( 2D ), on or before the`
  line `31st day of March, 2008;`
  line `( ii ) in respect of an application made on or after the 1st day of June, 2007 2 [but before the 1st day`
  line `of June, 2010], within twelve months from the end of the month in which the application was made;]`
  line `3 [( iii ) in respect of an application made on or after the 1st day of June, 2010, within eighteen`
  line `months from the end of the month in which the application was made.]`
  line `4 [( 5 ) Subject to the provisions of section 245BA, the materials brought on record before the`
  line `Settlement Commission shall be considered by the Members of the concerned Bench before passing any`
  line `order under sub-section ( 4 ) and, in relation to the passing of such order, the provisions of section 245BD`
  line `shall apply.]`
  line `( 6 ) Every order passed under sub-section ( 4 ) shall provide for the terms of settlement including any`
  line `demand by way of 5 [tax, penalty or interest], the manner in which any sum due under the settlement shall`
  line `be paid and all other matters to make the settlement effective and shall also provide that the settlement`
  line `shall be void if it is subsequently found by the Settlement Commission that it has been obtained by fraud`
  line `or misrepresentation of facts.`
  line `6 [( 6A ) Where any tax payable in pursuance of an order under sub-section ( 4 ) is not paid by the`
  line `assessee within thirty-five days of the receipt of a copy of the order by him, then, whether or not the`
  line `Settlement Commission has extended the time for payment of such tax or has allowed payment thereof by`
  line `instalments, the assessee shall be liable to pay simple interest at 7 [one and one-fourth per cent. for every`
  line `month or part of a month] on the amount remaining unpaid from the date of expiry of the period of`
  line `thirty-five days aforesaid.]`
  line `8 [( 6B ) The Settlement Commission may, with a view to rectifying any mistake apparent from the`
  line `record, amend any order passed by it under sub-section ( 4 ) —`
  line `( a ) at any time within a period of six months from the end of the month in which the order was`
  line `passed; or`
  line `( b ) at any time within the period of six months from the end of the month in which an application`
  line `for rectification has been made by the Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner or the applicant,`
  line `as the case may be:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 47, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2010).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 61 (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 61, ibid., for “tax or penalty” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1987).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 64, for “fifteen per cent. per annum” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2008).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 59, for sub-section ( 6B ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_713_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_714:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-714
  sectionNo (714)
  orderNo 714
  title `Page 714`
  content obj_root_law_sections_714_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_714_footnotes
  sourcePage 714
obj_root_law_sections_714_content:
  string
  line 714
  line `Provided that no application for rectification shall be made by the Principal Commissioner or the`
  line `Commissioner or the applicant after the expiry of six months from the end of the month in which an order`
  line `under sub-section ( 4 ) is passed by the Settlement Commission:`
  line `Provided further that an amendment which has the effect of modifying the liability of the applicant`
  line `shall not be made under this sub-section unless the Settlement Commission has given notice to the`
  line `applicant and the Principal Commissioner or Commissioner of its intention to do so and has allowed the`
  line `applicant and the Principal Commissioner or Commissioner an opportunity of being heard.]`
  line `( 7 ) Where a settlement becomes void as provided under sub-section ( 6 ), the proceedings with respect`
  line `to the matters covered by the settlement shall be deemed to have been revived from the stage at which the`
  line `application was allowed to be proceeded with by the Settlement Commission and the income-tax`
  line `authority concerned, may, notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act,`
  line `complete such proceedings at any time before the expiry of two years from the end of the financial year in`
  line `which the settlement became void.`
  line `1 [( 8 ) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that nothing contained in section 153 shall apply`
  line `to any order passed under sub-section ( 4 ) or to any order of assessment, reassessment or recomputation`
  line `required to be made by the 2 [Assessing Officer] in pursuance of any directions contained in such order`
  line `passed by the Settlement Commission 3 [and nothing contained in the proviso to sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 186 shall apply to the cancellation of the registration of a firm required to be made in pursuance of`
  line `any such directions as aforesaid.]]`
  line `4 [ 245DD. Power of Settlement Commission to order provisional attachment to protect`
  line `revenue. — ( 1 ) Where, during the pendency of any proceeding before it, the Settlement Commission is of`
  line `the opinion that for the purpose of protecting the interests of the revenue it is necessary so to do, it may,`
  line `by order, attach provisionally any property belonging to the applicant in the manner provided in the`
  line `Second Schedule:`
  line `Provided that where a provisional attachment made under section 281B is pending immediately`
  line `before an application is made under section 245C, an order under this sub-section shall continue such`
  line `provisional attachment up to the period up to which an order made under section 281B would have`
  line `continued if such application had not been made:`
  line `Provided further that where the Settlement Commission passes an order under this sub-section after`
  line `the expiry of the period referred to in the preceding proviso, the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) shall apply`
  line `to such order as if the said order had originally been passed by the Settlement Commission.`
  line `( 2 ) Every provisional attachment made by the Settlement Commission under sub-section ( 1 ) shall`
  line `cease to have effect after the expiry of a period of six months from the date of the order made under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ):`
  line `Provided that the Settlement Commission may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, extend the`
  line `aforesaid period by such further period or periods as it thinks fit 5 ***.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 61 (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `5. The words “, so, however, that the total period of extension shall not in any case exceed two years” omitted by`
  line `Act 22 of 2007, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1-6-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_714_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_715:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-715
  sectionNo (715)
  orderNo 715
  title `Page 715`
  content obj_root_law_sections_715_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_715_footnotes
  sourcePage 715
obj_root_law_sections_715_content:
  string
  line 715
  line `245E. Power of Settlement Commission to reopen completed proceedings. — If the Settlement`
  line `Commission is of the opinion (the reasons for such opinion to be recorded by it in writing) that, for the`
  line `proper disposal of the case pending before it, it is necessary or expedient to reopen any proceeding`
  line `connected with the case but which has been completed 1 *** under this Act by any income-tax authority`
  line `before the application under section 245C was made, it may, with the concurrence of the applicant,`
  line `reopen such proceeding and pass such order thereon as it thinks fit, as if the case in relation to which the`
  line `application for settlement had been made by the applicant under that section covered such proceeding`
  line `also:`
  line `2 [Provided that no proceeding shall be reopened by the Settlement Commission under this section if`
  line `the period between the end of the assessment year to which such a proceeding relates and the date of`
  line `application for settlement under section 245C exceeds nine years:]`
  line `3 [Provided further that no proceeding shall be reopened by the Settlement Commission under this`
  line `section in a case where an application under section 245C is made on or after the 1st day of June, 2007.]`
  line `245F. Powers and procedure of Settlement Commission. — ( 1 ) In addition to the powers conferred`
  line `on the Settlement Commission under this Chapter, it shall have all the powers which are vested in an`
  line `income-tax authority under this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) Where an application made under section 245C has been allowed to be proceeded with`
  line `under section 245D, the Settlement Commission shall, until an order is passed under sub-section ( 4 ) of`
  line `section 245D, have, subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 3 ) of that section, exclusive jurisdiction to`
  line `exercise the powers and perform the functions of an income-tax authority under this Act in relation to the`
  line `case:`
  line `4 [Provided that where an application has been made under section 245C on or after the 1st day of`
  line `June, 2007, the Settlement Commission shall have such exclusive jurisdiction from the date on which the`
  line `application was made:`
  line `Provided further that where —`
  line `( i ) an application made on or after the 1st day of June, 2007, is rejected under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 245D; or`
  line `( ii ) an application is not allowed to be proceeded with under sub-section ( 2A ) of section 245D, or,`
  line `as the case may be, is declared invalid under sub-section ( 2C ) of that section; or`
  line `( iii ) an application is not allowed to be further proceeded with under sub-section ( 2D ) of section`
  line 245D,
  line `the Settlement Commission, in respect of such application shall have such exclusive jurisdiction upto the`
  line `date on which the application is rejected, or, not allowed to be proceeded with, or, declared invalid, or,`
  line `not allowed to be further proceeded with, as the case may be.]`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 2 ) and in the absence of any express direction`
  line `to the contrary by the Settlement Commission, nothing contained in this section shall affect the operation`
  line `of any other provision of this Act requiring the applicant to pay tax on the basis of self-assessment 5 *** in`
  line `relation to the matters before the Settlement Commission.`
  line `( 4 ) For the removal of doubt, it is hereby declared that, in the absence of any express direction by the`
  line `Settlement Commission to the contrary, nothing in this Chapter shall affect the operation of the provisions`
  line `of this Act in so far as they relate to any matters other than those before the Settlement Commission.`
  line `6 [ 7 * * * * *`
  line `1. The word and figures “under the Indian Income - tax Act, 1922, or” omitted by Act 67 of 1984, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1 -10-1984).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 62, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 66 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 67, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `5. The words “or by way of advance tax” omitted by the 11 of 1987, s. 63 (w.e.f. 1 -6-1987).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 17, for sub-section ( 5 ) (w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
  line `7. Sub-sections ( 5 ) and ( 6 ) omitted by Act 11 of 1987, s. 63 (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_715_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_716:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-716
  sectionNo (716)
  orderNo 716
  title `Page 716`
  content obj_root_law_sections_716_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_716_footnotes
  sourcePage 716
obj_root_law_sections_716_content:
  string
  line 716
  line `( 7 ) The Settlement Commission shall, subject to the provisions of this Chapter, have power to`
  line `regulate its own procedure and the procedure of Benches thereof in all matters arising out of the exercise`
  line `of its powers or of the discharge of its functions, including the places at which the Benches shall hold`
  line `their sittings.]`
  line `245G. Inspection, etc., of reports. — No person shall be entitled to inspect, or obtain copies of, any`
  line `reports made by any income-tax authority to the Settlement Commission; but the Settlement Commission`
  line `may, in its discretion, furnish copies thereof to any such person on an application made to it in this behalf`
  line `and on payment of the prescribed fee:`
  line `Provided that, for the purpose of enabling any person whose case is under consideration to rebut any`
  line `evidence brought on record against him in any such report, the Settlement Commission shall, on an`
  line `application made in this behalf, and on payment of the prescribed fee by such person, furnish him with a`
  line `certified copy of any such report or part thereof relevant for the purpose.`
  line `245H. Power of Settlement Commission to grant immunity from prosecution and penalty. — ( 1 )`
  line `The Settlement Commission may, if it is satisfied that any person who made the application for settlement`
  line `under section 245C has co-operated with the Settlement Commission in the proceedings before it and has`
  line `made a full and true disclosure of his income and the manner in which such income has been derived,`
  line `grant to such person, subject to such conditions as it may think fit to impose 1 [for the reasons to be`
  line `recorded in writing], immunity from prosecution for any offence under this Act or under the Indian Penal`
  line `Code (45 of 1860) or under any other Central Act for the time being in force 2 [and also (either wholly or`
  line `in part) from the imposition of any penalty] under this Act, with respect to the case covered by the`
  line `settlement:`
  line `3 [Provided that no such immunity shall be granted by the Settlement Commission in cases where the`
  line `proceedings for the prosecution for any such offence have been instituted before the date of receipt of the`
  line `application under section 245C:]`
  line `4 [Provided further that the Settlement Commission shall not grant immunity from prosecution for any`
  line `offence under the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) or under any Central Act other than this Act and the`
  line `Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957) to a person who makes an application under section 245C on or after`
  line `the 1st day of June, 2007.]`
  line `3 [( 1A ) An immunity granted to a person under sub-section ( 1 ) shall stand withdrawnif such person`
  line `fails to pay any sum specified in the order of settlement passed under sub-section ( 4 ) of section`
  line `245D within the time specified in such order or within such further time as may be allowed by the`
  line `Settlement Commission, or fails to comply with any other condition subject to which the immunity was`
  line `granted and thereupon the provisions of this Act shall apply as if such immunity had not been granted.]`
  line `( 2 ) An immunity granted to a person under sub-section ( 1 ) may, at any time, be withdrawn by the`
  line `Settlement Commission, if it is satisfied that such person 5 *** had, in the course of the settlement`
  line `proceedings, concealed any particulars material to the settlement or had given false evidence, and`
  line `thereupon such person may be tried for the offence with respect to which the immunity was granted or for`
  line `any other offence of which he appears to have been guilty in connection with the settlement and shall also`
  line `become liable to the imposition of any penalty under this Act to which such person would have been`
  line `liable, had not such immunity been granted.`
  line `6 [ 245HA. Abatement of proceeding before Settlement Commission. — ( 1 ) Where —`
  line `( i ) an application made under section 245C on or after the 1st day of June, 2007 has been`
  line `rejected under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 245D; or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 60 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 43, for “and also from the imposition of any penalty” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1984).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 64 (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 68 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `5. The words “has not complied with the conditions subject to which the immunity was granted or that such person” omitted`
  line `by Act 11 of 1987, s. 64 (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 69 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007). Earlier section 245HA was inserted by Act 11 of 1987, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1-6-`
  line `1987) which was amended by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988) and later on omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 96 (w.e.f. 1-`
  line `6-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_716_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_717:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-717
  sectionNo (717)
  orderNo 717
  title `Page 717`
  content obj_root_law_sections_717_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_717_footnotes
  sourcePage 717
obj_root_law_sections_717_content:
  string
  line 717
  line `( ii ) an application made under section 245C has not been allowed to be proceeded with under`
  line `sub-section ( 2A ) or further proceeded with under sub-section ( 2D ) of section 245D; or`
  line `( iii ) an application made under section 245C has been declared as invalid under sub-section ( 2C )`
  line `of section 245D; or`
  line `1 [( iiia ) in respect of any application made under section 245C, an order under sub-section ( 4 )`
  line `of section 245D has been passed not providing for the terms of settlement; or]`
  line `( iv ) in respect of any other application made under section 245C, an order under sub-section ( 4 )`
  line `of section 245D has not been passed within the time or period specified under sub-section ( 4A )`
  line `of section 245D,`
  line `the proceedings before the Settlement Commission shall abate on the specified date.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, "specified date" means —`
  line `( a ) in respect of an application referred to in clause ( i ), the day on which the application was`
  line rejected;
  line `( b ) in respect of an application referred to in clause ( ii ), the 31st day of July, 2007;`
  line `( c ) in respect of an application referred to in clause ( iii ), the last day of the month in which the`
  line `application was declared invalid;`
  line `1 [( ca ) in respect of an application referred to clause ( iiia ), the day on which the order under sub-`
  line `section ( 4 ) of section 245D was passed not providing for the terms of settlement;]`
  line `( d ) in respect of an application referred to in clause ( iv ), on the date on which the time or period`
  line `specified in sub-section ( 4A ) of section 245D expires.`
  line `( 2 ) Where a proceeding before the Settlement Commission abates, the Assessing Officer, or, as the`
  line `case may be, any other income-tax authority before whom the proceeding at the time of making the`
  line `application was pending, shall dispose of the case in accordance with the provisions of this Act as if no`
  line `application under section 245C had been made.`
  line `( 3 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 2 ), the Assessing Officer, or, as the case may be, other income-`
  line `tax authority, shall be entitled to use all the material and other information produced by the assessee`
  line `before the Settlement Commission or the results of the inquiry held or evidence recorded by the`
  line `Settlement Commission in the course of the proceedings before it, as if such material, information,`
  line `inquiry and evidence had been produced before the Assessing Officer or other income-tax authority or`
  line `held or recorded by him in the course of the proceedings before him.`
  line `( 4 ) For the purposes of the time-limit under sections 149, 153, 153B, 154, 155, 158BE and 231 and`
  line `for the purposes of payment of interest under section 243 or 244 or, as the case may be, section 244A, for`
  line `making the assessment or reassessment under sub-section ( 2 ), the period commencing on and from the`
  line `date of the application to the Settlement Commission under section 245C and ending with “specified`
  line `date” referred to in sub -section ( 1 ) shall be excluded; and where the assessee is a firm, for the purposes of`
  line `the time-limit for cancellation of registration of the firm under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 186, the period`
  line `aforesaid shall, likewise, be excluded.`
  line `245HAA. Credit for tax paid in case of abatement of proceedings. — Where an application made`
  line `under section 245C on or after the 1st day of June, 2007, is rejected under sub-section ( 1 ) of section`
  line `245D, or any other application made under section 245C is not allowed to be proceeded with under`
  line `sub-section ( 2A ) of section 245D or is declared invalid under sub-section ( 2C ) of section 245D or has not`
  line `been allowed to be further proceeded with under sub-section ( 2D ) of section 245D or an order under`
  line `sub-section ( 4 ) of section 245D has not been passed within the time or period specified under`
  line `sub-section ( 4A ) of section 245D, the Assessing Officer shall allow the credit for the tax and interest paid`
  line `on or before the date of making the application or during the pendency of the case before the Settlement`
  line Commission.]
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 61 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_717_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_718:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-718
  sectionNo (718)
  orderNo 718
  title `Page 718`
  content obj_root_law_sections_718_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_718_footnotes
  sourcePage 718
obj_root_law_sections_718_content:
  string
  line 718
  line `245-I. Order of settlement to be conclusive. — Every order of settlement passed under sub-section`
  line `( 4 ) of section 245D shall be conclusive as to the matters stated therein and no matter covered by such`
  line `order shall, save as otherwise provided in this Chapter, be reopened in any proceeding under this Act or`
  line `under any other law for the time being in force.`
  line `245J. Recovery of sums due under order of settlement. — Any sum specified in an order of`
  line `settlement passed under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 245D may, subject to such conditions, if any, as may`
  line `be specified therein, be recovered, and any penalty for default in making payment of such sum may be`
  line `imposed and recovered in accordance with the provisions of Chapter XVII, by the 1 [Assessing Officer]`
  line `having jurisdiction over the person who made the application for settlement under section 245C.`
  line `2 [ 245K. Bar on subsequent application for settlement. — ( 1 ) Where —`
  line `( i ) an order of settlement passed under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 245D provides for the`
  line `imposition of a penalty on the person who made the application under section 245C for settlement, on`
  line `the ground of concealment of particulars of his income; or`
  line `( ii ) after the passing of an order of settlement under the said sub-section ( 4 ) in relation to a case,`
  line `such person is convicted of any offence under Chapter XXII in relation to that case; or`
  line `( iii ) the case of such person was sent back to the Assessing Officer by the Settlement`
  line `Commission on or before the 1st day of June, 2002,`
  line `then, 3 [he or any person related to such person (herein referred to as related person) shall not be entitled to`
  line `apply] for settlement under section 245C in relation to any other matter.`
  line `( 2 ) Where a person has made an application under section 245C on or after the 1st day of June, 2007`
  line `and if such application has been allowed to be proceeded with under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 245D,`
  line `such person 4 [or any related person shall not be subsequently entitled] to make an application under`
  line `section 245C.]`
  line `5 [ Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, “related person” with respect to a person means,—`
  line `( i ) where such person is an individual, any company in which such person holds more than fifty`
  line `per cent of the shares or voting rights at any time, or any firm or association of persons or body of`
  line `individuals in which such person is entitled to more than fifty per cent of the profits at any time, or`
  line `any Hindu undivided family in which such person is a karta;`
  line `( ii ) where such person is a company, any individual who held more than fifty per cent of the`
  line `shares or voting rights in such company at any time before the date of application before the`
  line `Settlement Commission by such person;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 70, for section 245K (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 62, for “he shall not be entitled to apply” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2015).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 62, ibid., for “shall not be subsequently entitled” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2015).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 62, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_718_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_719:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-719
  sectionNo (719)
