obj_root_law_sections_720_content:
  string
  line 720
  line `1 [( iv ) a determination or decision by the Authority whether an arrangement, which is`
  line `proposed to be undertaken by any person being a resident or a non-resident, is an impermissible`
  line `avoidance arrangement as referred to in Chapter X-A or not:]`
  line `2 [Provided that where an advance ruling has been pronounced, before the date on which the`
  line `Finance Act, 2003 receives the assent of the President, by the Authority in respect of an`
  line `application by a resident applicant referred to in sub-clause ( ii ) of this clause as it stood`
  line `immediately before such date, such ruling shall be binding on the persons specified in section`
  line 245S;]
  line `3 [( b ) “applicant” means—`
  line `( A ) any person who —`
  line `( I ) is a non-resident referred to in sub-clause ( i )of clause( a );or`
  line `( II ) is a resident referred to in sub-clause( ii )of clause( a ); or`
  line `( III ) is a resident referred to in sub-clause ( iia ) of clause ( a ) falling within any such`
  line `class or category of persons as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify; or`
  line `( IV ) is a resident falling within any such class or category of persons as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf; or`
  line `( V ) is referred to in sub-clause ( iv ) of clause ( a ),`
  line `and makes an application under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 245Q;`
  line `( B ) an applicant as defined in clause ( c ) of section 28E of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of`
  line `1962);`
  line `( C ) an applicant as defined in clause ( c ) of section 23A of the Central Excise Act, 1944 (1`
  line `of 1944);`
  line `( D ) an applicant as defined in clause ( b ) of section 96A of the Finance`
  line `Act, 1994 (32 of 1994);]]`
  line `( c ) “application” means an application made to the Authority under sub -section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 245Q;`
  line `( d ) “Authority” means the Authority for Advance Rulings constituted under section 245 -O;`
  line `( e ) “Chairman” means the Chairman of the Authority;`
  line `4 [( f ) “Member” means a Member of the Authority and includes the Chairman and`
  line Vice-chairman;
  line `( g ) “Vice - chairman” means the Vice -chairman of the Authority.]`
  line `245-O. Authority for Advance Rulings. — ( 1 ) The Central Government shall constitute an Authority`
  line `for giving advance rulings, to be known as “Authority for Advance Rulings”:`
  line `5 [Provided that the Authority shall cease to act as an Authority for Advance Rulings for the purposes`
  line `of Chapter V of the Customs Act, 1962 on and from the date of appointment of the Customs Authority for`
  line `Advance Rulings under section 28EA of that Act.]`
  line `5 [( 1A ) On and from the date of appointment of the Customs Authority for Advance Rulings referred`
  line `to in the proviso to sub-section (1), the Authority shall act as an Appellate Authority, for the purpose of`
  line `Chapter V of the Customs Act, 1962:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 53 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 92 (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 80 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 66, for clause ( f ) (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_720_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_721:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-721
  sectionNo (721)
  orderNo 721
  title `Page 721`
  content obj_root_law_sections_721_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_721_footnotes
  sourcePage 721
obj_root_law_sections_721_content:
  string
  line 721
  line `Provided that the Authority shall not admit any appeal against any ruling or order passed earlier by it`
  line `in the capacity of the Authority for Advance Rulings in relation to any matter under Chapter V of the`
  line `Customs Act, 1962 after the date of such appointment of the Customs Authority for Advance Rulings.]`
  line `1 [( 2 ) The Authority shall consist of a Chairman and such number of Vice-chairmen, revenue`
  line `Members and law Members as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint.`
  line `( 3 ) A person shall be qualified for appointment as —`
  line `( a ) Chairman, who has been a Judge of the Supreme Court 2 [or the Chief Justice of a High Court`
  line `or for at least seven years a Judge of a High Court];`
  line `( b ) Vice-chairman, who has been Judge of a High Court;`
  line `3 [( c ) a revenue Member —`
  line `( i ) from the Indian Revenue Service, who is, or is qualified to be, a Member of the Board; or`
  line `( ii ) from the Indian Customs and Central Excise Service, who is, or is qualified to be, a`
  line `Member of the Central Board of Excise and Customs,`
  line `on the date of occurrence of vacancy; ]`
  line `4 [( d ) a law Member from the Indian Legal Service, who is, or is qualified to be, an Additional`
  line `Secretary to the Government of India 2 [on the date of occurrence of vacancy ].]`
  line `( 4 ) The terms and conditions of service and the salaries and allowances payable to the Members shall`
  line `be such as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 5 ) The Central Government shall provide to the Authority with such officers and employees, as may`
  line `be necessary, for the efficient discharge of the functions of the Authority under this Act.`
  line `( 6 ) The powers and functions of the Authority may be discharged by its Benches as may be`
  line `constituted by the Chairman from amongst the Members thereof.`
  line `2 [ ( 6A ) In the event of the occurrence of any vacancy in the office of the Chairman by reason of his`
  line `death, resignation or otherwise, the senior-most Vice-chairman shall act as the Chairman until the date on`
  line `which a new Chairman, appointed in accordance with the provisions of this Act to fill such vacancy,`
  line `enters upon his office.`
  line `( 6B ) In case the Chairman is unable to discharge his functions owing to absence, illness or any other`
  line `cause, the senior-most Vice-Chairman shall discharge the functions of the Chairman until the date on`
  line `which the Chairman resumes his duties. ]`
  line `( 7 ) A Bench shall consist of the Chairman or the Vice-chairman and one revenue Member and one`
  line `law Member:`
  line `5 [Provided that where the Authority is dealing with an application seeking advance ruling in any`
  line `matter relating to this Act, the revenue Member of the Bench shall be such Member as referred to in`
  line `sub-clause ( i ) of clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 3 ).]`
  line `( 8 ) The Authority shall be located in the National Capital Territory of Delhi and its Benches shall be`
  line `located at such places as the Central Government may, by notification specify.]`
  line `6 [ 245-OA. Qualifications, terms and conditions of service of Chairman, Vice-Chairman and`
  line `Member. — Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the qualifications, appointment, term of`
  line `office, salaries and allowances, resignation, removal and the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Chairman, Vice-Chairman and other Members of the Authority appointed after the commencement of`
  line `Part XIV of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017, shall be governed by the provisions of section 184 of`
  line `that Act:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 67, for sub-sections ( 2 ), ( 3 ), ( 4 ) and ( 5 ) (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 81 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 81, ibid., for clause ( c ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 63, for clause ( d ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 174 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_721_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_722:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-722
  sectionNo (722)
  orderNo 722
  title `Page 722`
  content obj_root_law_sections_722_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_722_footnotes
  sourcePage 722
obj_root_law_sections_722_content:
  string
  line 722
  line `Provided that the Chairman, Vice-Chairman and Member appointed before the commencement of`
  line `Part XIV of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017, shall continue to be governed by the provisions of this`
  line `Act and the rules made thereunder as if the provisions of section 184 of the Finance Act, 2017 had not`
  line `come into force.]`
  line `245P. Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings. — No proceeding before, or pronouncement of`
  line `advance ruling by, the Authority shall be questioned or shall be invalid on the ground merely of the`
  line `existence of any vacancy or defect in the constitution of the Authority.`
  line `245Q. Applicationfor advance ruling. — ( 1 ) An applicant desirous of obtaining an advance ruling`
  line `under this Chapter 1 [ 2 * ** or under Chapter IIIA of the Central Excise Act, 1944 (1 of 1944) or under`
  line `Chapter VA of the Finance Act, 1994 (32 of 1994) ] may make an application in such form and in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed, stating the question on which the advance ruling is sought.`
  line `( 2 ) The application shall be made in quadruplicate and be accompanied by a fee of 3 [ten thousand`
  line `rupees or such fee as may be prescribed in this behalf, whichever is higher].`
  line `( 3 ) An applicant may withdraw an application within thirty days from the date of the application.`
  line `245R. Procedure on receipt of application. — ( 1 ) On receipt of an application, the Authority shall`
  line `cause a copy thereof to be forwarded to the 4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] and, if`
  line `necessary, call upon him to furnish the relevant records:`
  line `Provided that where any records have been called for by the Authority in any case, such records shall,`
  line `as soon as possible, be returned to the 3 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner].`
  line `( 2 ) The Authority may, after examining the application and the records called for, by order, either`
  line `allow or reject the application:`
  line `5 [Provided that the Authority shall not allow the application where the question raised in the`
  line `application, —`
  line `( i ) is already pending before any income-tax authority or Appellate Tribunal [except in the case`
  line `of a resident applicant falling in sub-clause ( iii ) of clause ( b ) of section 245N] or any court;`
  line `( ii ) involves determination of fair market value of any property;`
  line `( iii ) relates to a transaction or issue which is designed prima facie for the avoidance of income-`
  line `tax [except in the case of a resident applicant falling in sub-clause ( iii ) of clause ( b ) ofsection`
  line `245N 6 *** 7 [or in the case of an applicant falling in sub-clause ( iiia ) of clause ( b ) of section 245N]]:]`
  line `Provided further that no application shall be rejected under this sub-section unless an opportunity`
  line `has been given to the applicant of being heard:`
  line `Provided also that where the application is rejected, reasons for such rejection shall be given in`
  line `the order.`
  line `( 3 ) A copy of every order made under sub-section ( 2 ) shall be sent to the applicant and to the`
  line `3 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner].`
  line `( 4 ) Where an application is allowed under sub-section ( 2 ), the Authority shall, after examining such`
  line `further material as may be placed before it by the applicant or obtained by the Authority, pronounce its`
  line `advance ruling on the question specified in the application.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 82 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `2. The words and figures “or under Chapter V of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962)” shall stand omitted (date to be`
  line `notified) by Act 13 of 2018, s. 51.`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 92, for “two thousand five hundred rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 64, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-6-2000).`
  line `6. The words “or in the case of an applicant falling in sub-clause ( iiia ) of clause ( b ) of section 245N” omitted by Act 17 of`
  line `2013, s. 54 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `7. Ins. by s. 54, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_722_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_723:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-723
  sectionNo (723)
  orderNo 723
  title `Page 723`
  content obj_root_law_sections_723_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_723_footnotes
  sourcePage 723
obj_root_law_sections_723_content:
  string
  line 723
  line `( 5 ) On a request received from the applicant, the Authority shall, before pronouncing its advance`
  line `ruling, provide an opportunity to the applicant of being heard, either in person or through a duly`
  line `authorised representative.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-sectio n, “authorised representative” shall have the`
  line `meaning assigned to it in sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288, as if the applicant were an assessee.`
  line `( 6 ) The Authority shall pronounce its advance ruling in writing within six months of the receipt of`
  line application.
  line `( 7 ) A copy of the advance ruling pronounced by the Authority, duly signed by the Members and`
  line `certified in the prescribed manner shall be sent to the applicant and to the 1 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner], as soon as may be, after such pronouncement.`
  line `2 [ 245RR.Appellate authority not to proceed in certain cases. — No income-tax authority or the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal shall proceed to decide any issue in respect to which an application has been made by`
  line `an applicant, being a resident, 3 [under sub-section( 1 ) of section 245Q]].`
  line `245S. Applicability of advance ruling. — ( 1 ) The advance ruling pronounced by the Authority`
  line `under section 245R shall be binding only —`
  line `( a ) on the applicant who had sought it;`
  line `( b ) in respect of the transaction in relation to which the ruling had been sought; and`
  line `( c ) on the 1 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner], and the income-tax authorities`
  line `subordinate to him, in respect of the applicant and the said transaction.`
  line `( 2 ) The advance ruling referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be binding as aforesaid unless there is a`
  line `change in law or facts on the basis of which the advance ruling has been pronounced.`
  line `245T. Advance ruling to be void in certain circumstances. — ( 1 ) Where the Authority finds, on a`
  line `representation made to it by the 1 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] or otherwise, that an`
  line `advance ruling pronounced by it under sub-section ( 6 ) of section 245R has been obtained by the applicant`
  line `by fraud or misrepresentation of facts, it may, by order, declare such ruling to be void ab initio and`
  line `thereupon all the provisions of this Act shall apply (after excluding the period beginning with the date of`
  line `such advance ruling and ending with the date of order under this sub-section) to the applicant as if such`
  line `advance ruling had never been made.`
  line `( 2 ) A copy of the order made under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be sent to the applicant and the 1 [Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner].`
  line `245U.Powers of the Authority. — ( 1 ) The Authority shall, for the purpose of exercising its powers,`
  line `have all the powers of a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) as are referred to`
  line `in section 131 of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) The Authority shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of section 195, but not for the`
  line `purposes of Chapter XXVI, of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) and every proceeding`
  line `before the Authority shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the meaning of sections 193 and`
  line `228, and for the purpose of section 196, of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line `245V. Procedure of Authority. — The Authority shall, subject to the provisions of this Chapter, have`
  line `power to regulate its own procedure in all matters arising out of the exercise of its powers under this Act.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 o f 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 48 (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 52, for “under sub -section ( 1 ) of section 245R” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
obj_root_law_sections_723_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_724:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-724
  sectionNo (724)
  orderNo 724
  title `Page 724`
  content obj_root_law_sections_724_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_724_footnotes
  sourcePage 724
obj_root_law_sections_724_content:
  string
  line 724
  line `CHAPTER XX`
  line `A PPEALSAND REVISION`
  line `1 [ A. — Appeals 2 *** to the Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) and Commissioner (Appeals)`
  line `246.Appealable orders. — ( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ), any assessee aggrieved by`
  line `any of the following orders of an Assessing Officer (other than the Deputy Commissioner) may appeal to`
  line `the Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) 3 [before the 1st day of June, 2000] against such order —`
  line `( a ) an order against the assessee, where the assessee denies his liability to be assessed under this`
  line `Act 4 [or an intimation under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 1B ) of section 143, where the assessee`
  line `objects to the making of adjustments,] or any order of assessment under sub-section ( 3 ) of`
  line `section 143 or section 144, where the assessee objects to the amount of income assessed, or to the`
  line `amount of tax determined, or to the amount of loss computed, or to the status under which he is`
  line assessed;
  line `( b ) an order of assessment, reassessment or recomputation under section 147 or section 150;`
  line `( c ) an order under section 154 or section 155 having the effect of enhancing the assessment or`
  line `reducing a refund or an order refusing to allow the claim made by the assessee under either of the said`
  line sections;
  line `( d ) an order made under section 163 treating the assessee as the agent of a non-resident;`
  line `( e ) an order under sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-section ( 3 ) of section 170;`
  line `( f ) an order under section 171;`
  line `( g ) any order under clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) or under sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-section ( 3 ) or`
  line `sub-section ( 5 ) of section 185 5 *** 6 [in respect of any assessment for the assessment year`
  line `commencing on or before the 1st day of April, 1992];`
