obj_root_law_sections_726_content:
  string
  line 726
  line `( e ) an order imposing a penalty under section 271B 1 [or section 271BB];`
  line `2 [( ee ) an order made by a Deputy Commissioner imposing a penalty under section 271C,`
  line `section 271D or section 271E;]`
  line `( f ) an order made by a Deputy Commissioner or a Deputy Director imposing a penalty`
  line `under section 272A;`
  line `3 [( ff ) an order made by a Deputy Commissioner imposing a penalty under section 272AA;]`
  line `4 [( g ) an order imposing a penalty under Chapter XXI by the Income-tax Officer or the Assistant`
  line `Commissioner where such penalty has been imposed with the previous approval of the Deputy`
  line `Commissioner under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 274;]`
  line `( h ) an order made by an Assessing Officer (other than Deputy Commissioner) under the`
  line `provisions of this Act in the case of such person or classes of persons as the Board may, having`
  line `regard to the nature of the cases, the complexities involved and other relevant considerations, direct.`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), the Board or the 5 [Principal Director`
  line `General or Director General], or the 6 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or`
  line `7 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] if so authorised by the Board, may, by order in writing,`
  line `transfer any appeal which is pending before a Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) and any matter arising out`
  line `of or connected with such appeal and which is so pending, to the Commissioner (Appeals) if the Board or,`
  line `as the case may be, the 5 [Principal Director General or Director General] or 6 [Principal Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 7 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] (at the request of`
  line `the appellant or otherwise) is satisfied that it is necessary or expedient so to do having regard to the nature`
  line `of the case, the complexities involved and other relevant considerations and the Commissioner (Appeals)`
  line `may proceed with such appeal or matter, from the stage at which it was before it was so transferred:`
  line `Provided that the appellant may demand that before proceeding further with the appeal or matter, the`
  line `previous proceeding or any part thereof be re-opened or that he be reheard.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “appointed day” means the 10th day of July, 1 978, being the day appointed under`
  line `section 39 of the Finance (No. 2) Act, 1977 (29 of 1977);`
  line `( b ) “status” means the category under which the assessee is assessed as “individual”, “Hindu`
  line `undivided family” and so on.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 41, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 43 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 43, ibid., for clause ( g ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Director General” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
