  line 727
  line `1 [ 246A. Appealable orders before Commissioner (Appeals). — ( 1 ) 2 [Any assessee or any deductor`
  line `3 [or any collector] aggrieved] by any of the following orders (whether made before or after the appointed`
  line `day) may appeal to the Commissioner (Appeals) against —`
  line `( a ) 4 [an order passed by a Joint Commissioner under clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 3 ) of section`
  line `115VP or an order against the assessee] where the assessee denies his liability to be assessed under`
  line `this Act or an intimation under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 1B ) of 5 [section 143 or 6 [sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) of section 200A or sub-section ( 1 ) of section 206CB, where the assessee or the deductor or the`
  line `collector] objects] to the making of adjustments, or any order of assessment under sub-section ( 3 )`
  line `of section 143 7 [except an order passed in pursuance of directions of the Dispute Resolution Panel`
  line `8 *** 9 [or an order referred to in sub-section ( 12 ) of section 144BA]] or section 144, to the income`
  line `assessed, or to the amount of tax determined, or to the amount of loss computed, or to the status under`
  line `which he is assessed;`
  line `10 [( aa ) an order of assessment under sub-section ( 3 ) of section 115WE or section 115WF, where`
  line `the assessee, being an employer objects to the value of fringe benefits assessed;`
  line `( ab ) an order of assessment or reassessment under section 115WG;`
  line `( b ) an order of assessment, reassessment or recomputation under section 147 7 [except anorder`
  line `passed in pursuance of directions of the Dispute Resolution Panel 8 *** 9 [or an order referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 12 ) of section 144BA]] or section 150;`
  line `11 [( ba ) an order of assessment or reassessment 12 [under section 153A 7 [except an order passed in`
  line `pursuance of directions of the 13 [Dispute Resolution Panel]] 8 *** 9 [or an order referred to in sub-`
  line `section ( 12 ) ofsection 144BA];]`
  line `14 [( bb ) an order of assessment or reassessment under sub-section ( 3 ) of section 92CD;]`
  line `( c ) an order made under section 154 or section 155 having the effect of enhancing the assessment`
  line `or reducing a refund or an order refusing to allow the claim made by the assessee under either of the`
  line `said sections 15 *** 9 [except an order referred to in sub-section ( 12 ) of section 144BA];`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 49 (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 94, for “Any assessee aggrieved” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 64, (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 53, for “an order against the assessee” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2004).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 94, for “section 143, where the assessee objects” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 64, for “sub -section ( 1 ) of section 200A, where the a ssessee or the deductor” (w.e.f. 1 -6-`
  line `2015).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 94, for “except an order passed in pursuance of directions of the Dispute Resolution Panel”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `8. The words, brackets, figures and letters “or an order r eferred to in sub-section ( 12 ) of section 144BA” omitted by`
  line `Act 17 of 2013, s. 55 (w.e.f. 1-4-2013).`
  line `9. Ins. by s. 55, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 57 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `11. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 93 (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line `12. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 94, for “under section 153A” (w.r.e.f. 1 -10-2009).`
  line `13. Subs. by s. 94, ibid., for “Dispute Resolution Panel” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `14. Ins. by s. 94, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `15. The words, brackets, figures and letters “except where it is in respect of an order as referred to in sub -section ( 12 ) of`
  line `section 144BA” omitted by Act 17 of 2013, s. 55 (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
