obj_root_law_sections_729_content:
  string
  line 729
  line `( o ) an order made by a Deputy Commissioner or a Deputy Director imposing a penalty`
  line `under section 272A;`
  line `( p ) an order made by a Deputy Commissioner imposing a penalty under section 272AA;`
  line `( q ) an order imposing a penalty under Chapter XXI;`
  line `( r ) an order made by an Assessing Officer other than a Deputy Commissioner under the`
  line `provisions of this Act in the case of such person or class of persons, as the Board may, having regard`
  line `to the nature of the cases, the complexities involved and other relevant considerations, direct.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, where on or after the 1st day of October, 1998,`
  line `the post of Deputy Commissioner has been redesignated as Joint Commissioner and the post of Deputy`
  line `Director has been redesignated as Joint Director, the references in this sub- section for “Deputy`
  line `Commissioner” and “Deputy Director” shall be substituted by “Joint Commissioner” and “Joint Director”`
  line respectively.
  line `1 [( 1A ) Every appeal filed by an assessee in default against an order under section 201 on or after the`
  line `1st day of October, 1998 but before the 1st day of June, 2000 shall be deemed to have been filed under`
  line `this section.]`
  line `2 [( 1B ) Every appeal filed by an assessee in default against an order under sub-section ( 6A ) of section`
  line `206C on or after the 1st day of April, 2007 but before the 1st day of June, 2007 shall be deemed to have`
  line `been filed under this section.]`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 246, every appeal under this Act`
  line `which is pending immediately before the appointed day, before the Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) and`
  line `any matter arising out of or connected with such appeals and which is so pending shall stand transferred`
  line `on that date to the Commissioner (Appeals) and the Commissioner (Appeals) may proceed with such`
  line `appeal or matter from the stage at which it was on that day:`
  line `Provided that the appellant may demand that before proceeding further with the appeal or matter, the`
  line `previous proceeding or any part thereof be reopened or that he be re-heard.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, “appointed day” means the day appointed by the`
  line `Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette.]`
  line `247. [ Appeal by partner]. — Omitted by the Finance Act, 1992 (18 of 1992), s. 84 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `3 [ 248. Appeal by a person denying liability to deduct tax in certain cases. — Where under an`
  line `agreement or other arrangement, the tax deductible on any income, other than interest, under`
  line `section 195 is to be borne by the person by whom the income is payable, and such person having paid`
  line `such tax to the credit of the Central Government, claims that no tax was required to be deducted on such`
  line `income, he may appeal to the Commissioner (Appeals) for a declaration that no tax was deductible on`
  line `such income.]`
  line `249. Form of appeal and limitation. ( 1 ) Every appeal under this Chapter shall be in the prescribed`
  line `form and shall be verified in the prescribed manner 4 [and shall, in case of an appeal made to the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals) on or after the 1st day of October, 1998, irrespective of the date of initiation of`
  line `the assessment proceedings relating thereto be accompanied by a fee of, —`
  line `( i ) where the total income of the assessee as computed by the Assessing Officer in the case to`
  line `which the appeal relates is one hundred thousand rupees or less, two hundred fifty rupees;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 66 (w.e.f. 1-6-2000).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 71 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 72, ibid., for section 248 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007). Earlier it was substituted by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the fifth`
  line `Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
