obj_root_law_sections_730_content:
  string
  line 730
  line `( ii ) where the total income of the assessee, computed as aforesaid, in the case to which the appeal`
  line `relates is more than one hundred thousand rupees but not more than two hundred thousand rupees,`
  line `five hundred rupees;`
  line `( iii ) where the total income of the assessee, computed as aforesaid, in the case to which the appeal`
  line `relates is more than two hundred thousand rupees, one thousand rupees;]`
  line `1 [( iv ) where the subject matter of an appeal is not covered under clauses ( i ), ( ii ) and ( iii ), two`
  line `hundred fifty rupees.]`
  line `( 2 ) The appeal shall be presented within thirty days of the following date, that is to say, —`
  line `2 [( a ) where the appeal is under section 248, the date of payment of the tax, or]`
  line `3 [( b ) where the appeal relates to any assessment or penalty, the date of service of the notice of`
  line `demand relating to the assessment or penalty:`
  line `Provided that, where an application has been made under section 146 for reopening an`
  line `assessment, the period from the date on which the application is made to the date on which the order`
  line `passed on the application is served on the assessee shall be 4 [excluded: ]]`
  line `5 [Provided further that where an application has been made under sub-section ( 1 ) of section`
  line `270AA, the period beginning from the date on which the application is made, to the date on which the`
  line `order rejecting the application is served on the assessee, shall be excluded or:]`
  line `( c ) in any other case, the date on which intimation of the order sought to be appealed against is`
  line served.
  line `6 [( 2A ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 2 ), where an order has been made under`
  line `section 201 on or after the 1st day of October, 1998 but before the 1st day of June, 2000 and the assessee`
  line `in default has not presented any appeal within the time specified in that sub-section, he may present such`
  line `appeal before the 1st day of July, 2000.]`
  line `( 3 ) The 7 [*** Commissioner (Appeals)] may admit an appeal after the expiration of the said period if`
  line `he is satisfied that the appellant had sufficient cause for not presenting it within that period.`
  line `8 [( 4 ) No appeal under this Chapter shall be admitted unless at the time of filing of the appeal, —`
  line `( a ) where a return has been filed by the assessee, the assessee has paid the tax due on the income`
  line `returned by him; or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 83 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 73, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 59, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 93, for “excluded, or” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `5. The proviso inserted by s. 93, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 67 (w.e.f. 1-6-2000).`
  line `7. The words and brackets “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or, as the case may be, the” omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 50`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-10- 1998). Earlier “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)” was substituted for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner”`
  line `by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-198) and the words and b rackets “or, as the case may be, the Commissioner (Appeals)”`
  line `were inserted by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 59 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
