obj_root_law_sections_731_content:
  string
  line 731
  line `( b ) where no return has been filed by the assessee, the assessee has paid an amount equal to the`
  line `amount of advance tax which was payable by him:`
  line `Provided that, 1 [in a case falling under clause ( b ) and] on an application made by the appellant in`
  line `this behalf, the 2 [*** Commissioner (Appeals)] may, for any good and sufficient reason to be`
  line `recorded in writing, exempt him from the operation of the provisions of 3 [that clause].]`
  line `250. Procedure in appeal. — ( 1 ) The 4 [*** Commissioner (Appeals)] shall fix a day and place for the`
  line `hearing of the appeal, and shall give notice of the same to the appellant and to the 5 [Assessing Officer]`
  line `against whose order the appeal is preferred.`
  line `( 2 ) The following shall have the right to be heard at the hearing of the appeal —`
  line `( a ) the appellant, either in person or by an authorised representative;`
  line `( b ) the 5 [Assessing Officer,] either in person or by a representative.`
  line `( 3 ) The 4 [*** Commissioner (Appeals)] shall have the power to adjourn the hearing of the appeal`
  line `from time to time.`
  line `( 4 ) The 4 [*** Commissioner (Appeals)] may, before disposing of any appeal, make such further`
  line `inquiry as he thinks fit, or may direct the 5 [Assessing Officer] to make further inquiry and report the result`
  line `of the same to the 4 [*** Commissioner (Appeals)].`
  line `( 5 ) The 4 [*** Commissioner (Appeals)] may, at the hearing of an appeal, allow the appellant to go`
  line `into any ground of appeal not specified in the grounds of appeal, if the 4 [*** Commissioner (Appeals)] is`
  line `satisfied that the omission of that ground from the form of appeal was not wilful or unreasonable.`
  line `( 6 ) The order of the 4 [*** Commissioner (Appeals)] disposing of the appeal shall be in writing and`
  line `shall state the points for determination, the decision thereon and the reason for the decision.`
  line `6 [( 6A ) In every appeal, the 4 [*** Commissioner (Appeals)], where it is possible, may hear and decide`
  line `such appeal within a period of one year from the end of the financial year in which such appeal is filed`
  line `before him under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 246A.]`
  line `( 7 ) On the disposal of the appeal, the 4 [*** Commissioner (Appeals)] shall communicate the order`
  line `passed by him to the assessee and to the 7 [ 8 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or`
  line `9 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]].`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. The w ords and brackets “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or, as the case may be, the” omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 50`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-10- 1998). Earlier “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)” was substituted for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner”`
  line `by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4- 198) and the words and brackets “or, as the case may be, the Commissioner (Appeals)”`
  line `were inserted by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 45, for “this sub - section” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `4. The words and brackets “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or, as the case may be, the” omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 65`
  line `(w.e.f.1-10- 1998). Earlier “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)” was substituted for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner”`
  line `by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4- 198) and the words and brackets “or, as the case may be, the Commissioner (Appeals)”`
  line `were inserted by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 84 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4 for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `9. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
