obj_root_law_sections_732:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-732
  sectionNo (732)
  orderNo 732
  title `Page 732`
  content obj_root_law_sections_732_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_732_footnotes
  sourcePage 732
obj_root_law_sections_732_content:
  string
  line 732
  line `251. Powers of the 1 [ *** Commissioner (Appeals)]. — ( 1 ) In disposing of an appeal, the 1 [***`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals)] shall have the following powers —`
  line `( a ) in an appeal against an order of assessment, he may confirm, reduce, enhance or annul the`
  line `assessment 2 ***;`
  line `3 [( aa ) in an appeal against the order of assessment in respect of which the proceeding before the`
  line `Settlement Commission abates under section 245HA, he may, after taking into consideration all the`
  line `material and other information produced by the assessee before, or the results of the inquiry held or`
  line `evidence recorded by, the Settlement Commission, in the course of the proceeding before it and such`
  line `other material as may be brought on his record, confirm, reduce, enhance or annul the assessment;]`
  line `( b ) in an appeal against an order imposing a penalty, he may confirm or cancel such order or vary`
  line `it so as either to enhance or to reduce the penalty;`
  line `( c ) in any other case, he may pass such orders in the appeal as he thinks fit.`
  line `( 2 ) The 1 [*** Commissioner (Appeals)] shall not enhance an assessment or a penalty or reduce the`
  line `amount of refund unless the appellant has had a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against such`
  line `enhancement or reduction.`
  line `Explanation. — In disposing of an appeal, the 1 [*** Commissioner (Appeals)] may consider and`
  line `decide any matter arising out of the proceedings in which the order appealed against was passed,`
  line `notwithstanding that such matter was not raised before the 1 [*** Commissioner (Appeals)] by the`
  line appellant.
  line `B. — Appeals to the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `252. Appellate Tribunal. — ( 1 ) The Central Government shall constitute an Appellate Tribunal`
  line `consisting of as many judicial and accountant members as it thinks fit to exercise the powers and`
  line `discharge the functions conferred on the Appellate Tribunal by this Act.`
  line `4 [( 2 ) A judicial member shall be a person who has for at least ten years held a judicial office in the`
  line `territory of India or who has been a member of the 5 [Indian Legal Service] and has held a post in`
  line `6 [Grade II] of that Service or any equivalent or higher post for at least three years or who has been an`
  line `advocate for at least ten years.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, —`
  line `( i ) in computing the period during which a person has held judicial office in the territory of India,`
  line `there shall be included any period, after he has held any judicial office, during which the person has`
  line `been an advocate or has held the office of a member of a Tribunal or any post, under the Union or a`
  line `State, requiring special knowledge of law;`
  line `1. The words and brackets “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or, as the case may be, the” omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 65`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-10- 1998). Earlier “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)” was substituted for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner”`
  line `by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4- 198) and the words and brackets “or, as the case may be, the Commissioner (Appeals)”`
  line `were inserted by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `2. The certain words omitted by Act 14 of 2001, s. 83 (w.e.f. 1-6-2001).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 49 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 16 of 1981, s. 18, for sub-section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1981).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 51, for “Central Legal Service” (w.e.f. 1 -8-1998).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 51, ibid., for “Grade I” (w.e.f. 1 -8-1998).`
