  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_733_footnotes
  sourcePage 733
obj_root_law_sections_733_content:
  string
  line 733
  line `( ii ) in computing the period during which a person has been an advocate, there shall be included`
  line `any period during which the person has held judicial office or the office of a member of a Tribunal or`
  line `any post, under the Union or a State, requiring special knowledge of law after he became an advocate.`
  line `( 2A ) An accountant member shall be a person who has for at least ten years been in the practice of`
  line `accountancy as a chartered accountant under the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949), or as a`
  line `registered accountant under any law formerly in force or partly as a registered accountant and partly as a`
  line `chartered accountant, or who has been a member of the Indian Income-tax Service, Group A and has held`
  line `the post of 1 [Additional Commissioner of Income-tax] or any equivalent or higher post for at least three`
  line years.]
  line `2 [( 3 ) The Central Government shall appoint —`
  line `( a ) a person who is a sitting or retired Judge of a High Court and who has completed not less than`
  line `seven years of service as a Judge in a High Court; or`
  line `( b ) 3 *** one of the Vice-Presidents of the Appellate Tribunal,`
  line `to be the President thereof.]`
  line `4 [( 4 ) The Central Government may appoint one or more members of the Appellate Tribunal to be the`
  line `Vice-President or, as the case may be, Vice-Presidents thereof.`
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `( 5 ) 6 [The 7 *** Vice-President] shall exercise such of the powers and perform such of the functions of`
  line `the President as may be delegated to him by the President by a general or special order in writing.]`
  line `8 [ 252A. Qualifications, terms and conditions of service of President, Vice-President and`
  line `Member. — Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the qualifications, appointment, term of`
  line `office, salaries and allowances, resignation, removal and the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `President, Vice-President and other Members of the Appellate Tribunal appointed after the`
  line `commencement of Part XIV of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017, shall be governed by the provisions`
  line `of section 184 of that Act:`
  line `Provided that the President, Vice-President and Member appointed before the commencement of Part`
  line `XIV of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017, shall continue to be governed by the provisions of this Act,`
  line `and the rules made thereunder as if the provisions of section 184 of the Finance Act, 2017 (7 of 2017) had`
  line `not come into force. ]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 51, for “Commissioner of Income - tax” (w.e.f. 1 -8-1998).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 56, for sub-section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
  line `3. The words “the Senior Vice - President or” omitted by Act 28 of 2016, s. 94 (w.e.f. 1 -6-2016).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `5. Sub-section ( 4A ) omitted by Act 28 of 2016, s. 94 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016). Which was inserted by Act 21 of 1984, s. 24`
  line `(w.e.f.1-4-1984).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 24, for “A Vice - President” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1984).`
  line `7. The words “Senior Vice - President or a” omitted by Act 28 of 2016, s. 94 (w.e.f. 1 -6-2016).`
  line `8. Section 252A shall stand inserted by Act 7 of 2017, s. 174.`
