  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_735_footnotes
  sourcePage 735
obj_root_law_sections_735_content:
  string
  line 735
  line `( 2 ) The 1 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] may, if he objects to any order passed by 2 [an`
  line `3 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 4 [before the 1st day of October, 1998] or, as the case may be, a`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals)] under 5 [section 154 or] section 250, direct the 6 [Assessing Officer] to appeal to`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal against the order.`
  line `7 * * * * *`
  line `( 3 ) Every appeal under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) shall be filed within sixty days of the date`
  line `on which the order sought to be appealed against is communicated to the assessee or to the 1 [Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner], as the case may be:`
  line `8 [Provided that in respect of any appeal under clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ), this sub-section shall have`
  line `effect as if for the words “sixty days”, the words “thirty days” had been substituted.]`
  line `9 * * * * *`
  line `10 [( 4 ) The Assessing Officer or the assessee, as the case may be, on receipt of notice that an appeal`
  line `against the order of the Commissioner (Appeals), has been preferred under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section`
  line `( 2 ) by the other party, may, notwithstanding that he may not have appealed against such order or any part`
  line `thereof, within thirty days of the receipt of the notice, file a memorandum of cross-objections, verified in`
  line `the prescribed manner, against any part of the order of the Commissioner (Appeals), and such`
  line `memorandum shall be disposed of by the Appellate Tribunal as if it were an appeal presented within the`
  line `time specified in sub-section ( 3 ). ]`
  line `( 5 ) The Appellate Tribunal may admit an appeal or permit the filing of a memorandum of`
  line `cross-objections after the expiry of the relevant period referred to in sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 4 ), if`
  line `it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not presenting it within that period.`
  line `11 [( 6 ) An appeal to the Appellate Tribunal shall be in the prescribed form and shall be verified in the`
  line `prescribed manner and shall, in the case of an appeal made, on or after the 1st day of October, 1998,`
  line `irrespective of the date of initiation of the assessment proceedings relating thereto, be accompanied by a`
  line `fee of, —`
  line `( a ) where the total income of the assessee as computed by the Assessing Officer, in the case to`
  line `which the appeal relates, is one hundred thousand rupees or less, five hundred rupees,`
  line `( b ) where the total income of the assessee, computed as aforesaid, in the case to which the appeal`
  line `relates is more than one hundred thousand rupees but not more than two hundred thousand rupees,`
  line `one thousand five hundred rupees,`
  line `( c ) where the total income of the assessee, computed as aforesaid, in the case to which the appeal`
  line `relates is more than two hundred thousand rupees, one per cent of the assessed income, subject to a`
  line `maximum of ten thousand rupees,`
  line `12 [( d ) where the subject matter of an appeal relates to any matter, other than those specified in`
  line `clauses ( a ), ( b ) and ( c ), five hundred rupees:]`
  line `13 [Provided that no fee shall be payable in the case of an appeal referred to in sub-section ( 2 ), or,`
  line `sub-section ( 2A ) as it stood before its amendment by the Finance Act, 2016, or, a memorandum of`
  line `cross objections referred to in sub-section ( 4 ).]`
  line `( 7 ) An application for stay of demand shall be accompanied by a fee of five hundred rupees.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule, for “an Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 10 -7-1978).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 52 (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 31 of 1964, s. 12 (w.e.f. 6-10-1964).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. Sub-section ( 2A ) omitted by Act 28 of 2016, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1-7-1995).`
  line `9. Sub-section ( 3A ) omitted by Act 28 of 2016, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `10. Subs. by s. 95, ibid., for sub-section ( 4 ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 52, for sub-section ( 6 ) (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line `12. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 85 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `13. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 95, for the proviso (w.r.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_735_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_736:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-736
  sectionNo (736)
  orderNo 736
  title `Page 736`
  content obj_root_law_sections_736_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_736_footnotes
  sourcePage 736
obj_root_law_sections_736_content:
  string
  line 736
  line `254. Orders of Appellate Tribunal. — ( 1 ) The Appellate Tribunal may, after giving both the parties`
  line `to the appeal an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit.`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `( 2 ) The Appellate Tribunal may, at any time within 2 [six months from the end of the month in which`
  line `the order was passed], with a view to rectifying any mistake apparent from the record, amend any order`
  line `passed by it under sub-section ( 1 ), and shall make such amendment if the mistake is brought to its notice`
  line `by the assessee or the 3 [Assessing Officer]:`
  line `Provided that an amendment which has the effect of enhancing an assessment or reducing a refund or`
  line `otherwise increasing the liability of the assessee, shall not be made under this sub-section unless the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal has given notice to the assessee of its intention to do so and has allowed the assessee a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard:`
  line `4 [Provided further that any application filed by the assessee in this sub-section on or after the 1st day`
  line `of October, 1998, shall be accompanied by a fee of fifty rupees.]`
  line `5 [( 2A ) In every appeal, the Appellate Tribunal, where it is possible, may hear and decide such appeal`
  line `within a period of four years from the end of the financial year in which such appeal is filed under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) 6 [or sub-section ( 2 )] 7 *** of section 253:`
  line `8 [Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may, after considering the merits of the application made by`
  line `the assessee, pass an order of stay in any proceedings relating to an appeal filed under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 253, for a period not exceeding one hundred and eighty days from the date of such order and`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal shall dispose of the appeal within the said period of stay specified in that order:`
  line `Provided further that where such appeal is not so disposed of within the said period of stay as`
  line `specified in the order of stay, the Appellate Tribunal may, on an application made in this behalf by the`
  line `assessee and on being satisfied that the delay in disposing of the appeal is not attributable to the assessee,`
  line `extend the period of stay, or pass an order of stay for a further period or periods as it thinks fit; so,`
  line `however, that the aggregate of the period originally allowed and the period or periods so extended or`
  line `allowed shall not, in any case, exceed three hundred and sixty-five days and the Appellate Tribunal shall`
  line `dispose of the appeal within the period or periods of stay so extended or allowed:`
  line `9 [Provided also that if such appeal is not so disposed of within the period allowed under the first`
  line `proviso or the period or periods extended or allowed under the second proviso, which shall not, in any`
  line `case, exceed three hundred and sixty-five days, the order of stay shall stand vacated after the expiry of`
  line `such period or periods, even if the delay in disposing of the appeal is not attributable to the assessee.]]`
  line `1. Sub-section ( 1A ) omitted by Act 45 of 1972, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-1-1973).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 96, for “four years from the date of the order” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2016).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 53 (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 86 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 68 (w.e.f. 1-6-2000).`
  line `7. The words, brackets, figure and letter “or sub -section ( 2A )” omitted by Act 28 of 2016, s. 96 (w.e.f. 1 -6-2016).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 75, for the provisos (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 50, for the third proviso (w.e.f. 1-10-2008).`
