  content obj_root_law_sections_737_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_737_footnotes
  sourcePage 737
obj_root_law_sections_737_content:
  string
  line 737
  line `( 2B ) The cost of any appeal to the Appellate Tribunal shall be at the discretion of that Tribunal.]`
  line `( 3 ) The Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of any orders passed under this section to the assessee`
  line `and to the 1 [ 2 *** 3 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]].`
  line `( 4 ) 4 [Save as provided in section 256 or section 260A ], orders passed by the Appellate Tribunal on`
  line `appeal shall be final.`
  line `255. Procedure of Appellate Tribunal. — ( 1 ) The powers and functions of the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `may be exercised and discharged by Benches constituted by the President of the Appellate Tribunal from`
  line `among the members thereof.`
  line `( 2 ) Subject to the provisions contained in sub-section ( 3 ), a Bench shall consist of one judicial`
  line `member and one accountant member.`
  line `( 3 ) The President or any other member of the Appellate Tribunal authorised in this behalf by the`
  line `Central Government may, sitting singly, dispose of any case which has been allotted to the Bench of`
  line `which he is a member and which pertains to an assessee whose total income as computed by the`
  line `5 [Assessing Officer] in the case does not exceed 6 [fifty lakh rupees], and the President may, for the`
  line `disposal of any particular case, constitute a Special Bench consisting of three or more members, one of`
  line `whom shall necessarily be a judicial member and one an accountant member.`
  line `( 4 ) If the members of a Bench differ in opinion on any point, the point shall be decided according to`
  line `the opinion of the majority, if there is a majority, but if the members are equally divided, they shall state`
  line `the point or points on which they differ, and the case shall be referred by the President of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal for hearing on such point or points by one or more of the other members of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal, and such point or points shall be decided according to the opinion of the majority of the`
  line `members of the Appellate Tribunal who have heard the case, including those who first heard it.`
  line `( 5 ) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Appellate Tribunal shall have power to regulate its own`
  line `procedure and the procedure of Benches thereof in all matters arising out of the exercise of its powers or`
  line `of the discharge of its functions, including the places at which the Benches shall hold their sittings.`
  line `( 6 ) The Appellate Tribunal shall, for the purpose of discharging its functions, have all the powers`
  line `which are vested in the income-tax authorities referred to in section 131, and any proceeding before the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the meaning of sections`
  line `193 and 228 and for the purpose of section 196 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), and the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal shall be deemed to be a civil court for all the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXXV of the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898).`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. The words “Chief Commissioner or” omitted by Act 49 of 1991, s. 67 (w.e.f. 27 -9-1991).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. The words, figures and letter shall stand substituted (date to be notified) by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and the Schedule to read`
  line `as “Save as provided in the National Tax Tribunal Act, 2005” ( This amendment has been struck down by the Supreme`
  line `Court’s Order dated 25th September, 2014 in the Madras Bar Association Vs. Union of India.) Earlier “ section`
  line `256 or section 260A ” was substituted for “section 256” by Act 27 of 1999, s. 86 (w.e.f. 1 -6-1999).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 97, for “fifteen lakh rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_737_footnotes:
