  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_739_footnotes
  sourcePage 739
obj_root_law_sections_739_content:
  string
  line 739
  line `1 [ 260. Decision of High Court or Supreme Court on the case stated. — ( 1 ) The High Court or the`
  line `Supreme Court upon hearing any such case shall decide the questions of law raised therein, and shall`
  line `deliver its judgment thereon containing the grounds on which such decision is founded, and a copy of the`
  line `judgment shall be sent under the seal of the Court and the signature of the Registrar to the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal which shall pass such orders as are necessary to dispose of the case conformably to such`
  line judgment.
  line `2 [( 1A ) Where the High Court delivers a judgment in an appeal filed before it under section 260A,`
  line `effect shall be given to the order passed on the appeal by the Assessing Officer on the basis of a certified`
  line `copy of the judgment.]`
  line `( 2 ) The costs of any reference to the High Court or the Supreme Court which shall not include the fee`
  line `for making the reference shall be in the discretion of the Court.]`
  line `3 [ CC. — Appeals to High Court`
  line `260A. Appeal to High Court. — ( 1 ) An appeal shall lie to the High Court from every order passed in`
  line `appeal by the Appellate Tribunal 4 [before the date of establishment of the National Tax Tribunal], if the`
  line `High Court is satisfied that the case involves a substantial question of law.`
  line `( 2 ) 5 [The 6 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or the 7 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner] or an assessee aggrieved by any order passed by the Appellate Tribunal may file an`
  line `appeal to the High Court and such appeal under this sub-section shall be — ]`
  line `( a ) filed within one hundred and twenty days from the date on which the order appealed against is`
  line `8 [received by the assessee or the 6 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or`
  line `7 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner];`
  line `9 * * * * *`
  line `( c ) in the form of a memorandum of appeal precisely stating therein the substantial question of`
  line `law involved.`
  line `10 [( 2A ) The High Court may admit an appeal after the expiry of the period of one hundred and twenty`
  line `days referred to in clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 2 ), if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not`
  line `filing the same within that period.]`
  line `( 3 ) Where the High Court is satisfied that a substantial question of law is involved in any case, it shall`
  line `formulate that question.`
  line `( 4 ) The appeal shall be heard only on the question so formulated, and the respondents shall, at the`
  line `hearing of the appeal, be allowed to argue that the case does not involve such question:`
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall be deemed to take away or abridge the power of the`
  line `court to hear, for reasons to be recorded, the appeal on any other substantial question of law not`
  line `formulated by it, if it is satisfied that the case involves such question.`
  line `1.The words in bracket shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and the Schedule (This Amendment`
  line `has been struck down by the Supreme Court’s Order dated 25th September, 2014 in the Madras Bar Association Vs.`
  line `Union of India).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 57 (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 58, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line `4. The words in bracket shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and the Schedule (This`
  line `Amendment has been struck down by the Supreme Court’s Order date d 25th September, 2014 in the Madras Bar`
  line `Association Vs. Union of India).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 87, for “An appeal under this sub -section shall be —” (w.e.f.1 -6-1999).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f.1 -6-2013).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 87, for “Communicated to the appellant” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1999).`
  line `9. Clause ( b ) omitted by s. 87, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 49 (w.r.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
obj_root_law_sections_739_footnotes:
