  title `Page 740`
  content obj_root_law_sections_740_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_740_footnotes
  sourcePage 740
obj_root_law_sections_740_content:
  string
  line 740
  line `( 5 ) The High Court shall decide the question of law so formulated and deliver such judgment thereon`
  line `containing the grounds on which such decision is founded and may award such cost as it deems fit.`
  line `( 6 ) The High Court may determine any issue which —`
  line `( a ) has not been determined by the Appellate Tribunal; or`
  line `( b ) has been wrongly determined by the Appellate Tribunal, by reason of a decision on such`
  line `question of law as is referred to in sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `1 [( 7 ) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of`
  line `1908), relating to appeals to the High Court shall, as far as may be, apply in the case of appeals under this`
  line section.]
  line `260B. Case before High Court to be heard by not less than two Judges. — ( 1 ) When an appeal has`
  line `been filed before the High Court under section 260A, it shall be heard by a bench of not less than two`
  line `Judges of the High Court, and shall be decided in accordance with the opinion of such Judges or of the`
  line `majority, if any, of such Judges.`
  line `( 2 ) Where there is no such majority, the Judges shall state the point of law upon which they differ and`
  line `the case shall then be heard upon that point only by one or more of the other Judges of the High Court and`
  line `such point shall be decided according to the opinion of the majority of the Judges who have heard the`
  line `case including those who first heard it.]`
  line `D. — Appeals to the Supreme Court`
  line `261. Appeal to Supreme Court. — An appeal shall lie to the Supreme Court from any judgment of`
  line `the High Court 2 [delivered 3 [before the establishment of the National Tax Tribunal] on a reference made`
  line `under section 256 against an order made under section 254 before the 1st day of October, 1998 or an`
  line `appeal made to High Court in respect of an order passed under section 254 on or after that date] in any`
  line `case which the High Court certifies to be a fit one for appeal to the Supreme Court.`
  line `262. Hearing before Supreme Court. — ( 1 ) The provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5`
  line `of 1908), relating to appeals to the Supreme Court shall, so far as may be, apply in the case of appeals`
  line `under section 261 as they apply in the case of appeals from decrees of a High Court:`
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect the provisions of sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 260 or section 265.`
  line `( 2 ) The costs of the appeal shall be in the discretion of the Supreme Court.`
  line `( 3 ) Where the judgment of the High Court is varied or reversed in the appeal, effect shall be given to`
  line `the order of the Supreme Court in the manner provided in section 260 in the case of a judgment of the`
  line `High Court.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 87 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 59, for the words and figures “delivered on a reference made under section 256”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line `3. The words in bracket shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and the ScheduleThis amendment`
  line `has been struck down by the Supreme Court’s Order dated 25th September, 2014 in the Madras Bar Association Vs.`
  line `Union of India.).`
obj_root_law_sections_740_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_741:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-741
  sectionNo (741)
  orderNo 741
  title `Page 741`
  content obj_root_law_sections_741_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_741_footnotes
  sourcePage 741
obj_root_law_sections_741_content:
  string
  line 741
  line `E. — Revision by the 1 [ Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]`
  line `263. Revision of orders prejudicial to revenue. — ( 1 ) The 1 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner] may call for and examine the record of any proceeding under this Act, and if he considers`
  line `that any order passed therein by the 2 [Assessing Officer] is erroneous in so far as it is prejudicial to the`
  line `interests of the revenue, he may, after giving the assessee an opportunity of being heard and after making`
  line `or causing to be made such inquiry as he deems necessary, pass such order thereon as the circumstances`
  line `of the case justify, including an order enhancing or modifying the assessment, or cancelling the`
  line `assessment and directing a fresh assessment.`
  line `3 [ 4 [ Explanation 1.] — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that, for the purposes of this`
  line `sub-section, —`
  line `( a ) an order passed 5 [on or before or after the 1st day of June, 1988] by the Assessing Officer`
  line `shall include —`
  line `( i ) an order of assessment made by the 6 [Assistant Commissioner or Deputy Commissioner]`
  line `or the Income-tax Officer on the basis of the directions issued by the 7 [Joint Commissioner] under`
  line `section 144A;`
  line `( ii ) an order made by the 7 [Joint Commissioner] in exercise of the powers or in the`
  line `performance of the functions of an Assessing Officer conferred on, or assigned to, him under the`
  line `orders or directions issued by the Board or by the 8 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner] or 9 [Principal Director General or Director General] or 1 [Principal Commissioner`
  line `or Commissioner] authorised by the Board in this behalf under section 120;`
  line `( b ) “record” 10 [shall include and shall be deemed always to have included] all records relating to`
  line `any proceeding under this Act available at the time of examination by the 1 [Principal Commissioner`
  line `or Commissioner];`
  line `( c ) where any order referred to in this sub-section and passed by the Assessing Officer had been`
  line `the subject matter of any appeal 5 [filed on or before or after the 1st day of June, 1988], the powers of`
  line `the 1 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] under this sub-section shall extend 11 [and shall be`
  line `deemed always to have extended] to such matters as had not been considered and decided in such`
  line appeal.]
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 44, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-6-1988).`
  line `4. The Explanation numbered as Explanation 1 thereof by Act 20 of 2015, s. 67 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 13 of 1989, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-6-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 3, for “Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `9. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Director General” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 13 of 1989, s. 23, for “includes” (1 -6-1988).`
  line `11. Ins. by s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_741_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_742:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-742
  sectionNo (742)
  orderNo 742
  title `Page 742`
  content obj_root_law_sections_742_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_742_footnotes
  sourcePage 742
obj_root_law_sections_742_content:
  string
  line 742
  line `1 [ Explanation 2. — For the purposes of this section, it is hereby declared that an order passed by the`
  line `Assessing Officer shall be deemed to be erroneous in so far as it is prejudicial to the interests of the`
  line `revenue, if, in the opinion of the Principal Commissioner or Commissioner, —`
  line `( a ) the order is passed without making inquiries or verification which should have been made;`
  line `( b ) the order is passed allowing any relief without inquiring into the claim;`
  line `( c ) the order has not been made in accordance with any order, direction or instruction issued by`
  line `the Board under section 119; or`
  line `( d ) the order has not been passed in accordance with any decision which is prejudicial to the`
  line `assessee, rendered by the jurisdictional High Court or Supreme Court in the case of the assessee or`
  line `any other person.]`
  line `2 [( 2 ) No order shall be made under sub-section ( 1 ) after the expiry of two years from the end of the`
  line `financial year in which the order sought to be revised was passed.]`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 2 ), an order in revision under this section may`
  line `be passed at any time in the case of an order which has been passed in consequence of, or to give effect`
  line `to, any finding or direction contained in an order of the Appellate Tribunal, 3 [National Tax Tribunal,] the`
  line `High Court or the Supreme Court.`
  line `Explanation. — In computing the period of limitation for the purposes of sub-section ( 2 ), the time`
  line `taken in giving an opportunity to the assessee to be reheard under the proviso to section 129 and any`
  line `period during which any proceeding under this section is stayed by an order or injunction of any court`
  line `shall be excluded.`
  line `264.Revision of other orders. — ( 1 ) In the case of any order other than an order to which section`
  line `263 applies passed by an authority subordinate to him, the 4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]`
  line `may, either of his own motion or on an application by the assessee for revision, call for the record of any`
  line `proceeding under this Act in which any such order has been passed and may make such inquiry or cause`
  line `such inquiry to be made and, subject to the provisions of this Act, may pass such order thereon, not being`
  line `an order prejudicial to the assessee, as he thinks fit.`
  line `( 2 ) The 4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] shall not of his own motion revise any order`
  line `under this section if the order has been made more than one year previously.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 67 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 47, for sub-section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line `3. The words in bracket shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and the Schedule (This amendment`
  line `has been struck down by the Su preme Court’s Order dated 25th September, 2014 in the Madras Bar Association Vs.`
  line `Union of India.).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_742_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_743:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-743
  sectionNo (743)
  orderNo 743
  title `Page 743`
  content obj_root_law_sections_743_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_743_footnotes
  sourcePage 743
obj_root_law_sections_743_content:
  string
  line 743
  line `( 3 ) In the case of an application for revision under this section by the assessee, the application must`
  line `be made within one year from the date on which the order in question was communicated to him or the`
  line `date on which he otherwise came to know of it, whichever is earlier:`
  line `Provided that the 1 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] may, if he is satisfied that the assessee`
  line `was prevented by sufficient cause from making the application within that period, admit an application`
  line `made after the expiry of that period.`
  line `( 4 ) The 1 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] shall not revise any order under this section in`
  line `the following cases —`
  line `( a ) where an appeal against the order lies to the 2 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 3 [or to the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals)] or to the Appellate Tribunal but has not been made and the time within`
  line `which such appeal may be made has not expired, or, in the case of an appeal 4 [to the Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals) or] to the Appellate Tribunal, the assessee has not waived his right of appeal; or`
  line `( b ) where the order is pending on an appeal before the 2 [Deputy Commissioner(Appeals)]; or`
  line `( c ) where the order has been made the subject of an appeal 4 [to the Commissioner (Appeals) or]`
  line `to the Appellate Tribunal.`
  line `( 5 ) Every application by an assessee for revision under this section shall be accompanied by 5 [a fee of`
  line `five hundred rupees].`
  line `6 [( 6 ) On every application by an assessee for revision under this sub-section, made on or after the 1st`
  line `day of October, 1998, an order shall be passed within one year from the end of the financial year in which`
  line `such application is made by the assessee for revision.`
  line `Explanation. — In computing the period of limitation for the purposes of this sub-section, the time`
  line `taken in giving an opportunity to the assessee to be re-heard under the proviso to section 129 and any`
  line `period during which any proceeding under this section is stayed by an order or injunction of any court`
  line `shall be excluded.`
  line `( 7 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 6 ), an order in revision under sub-section ( 6 )`
  line `may be passed at any time in consequence of or to give effect to any finding or direction contained in an`
  line `order of the Appellate Tribunal, 7 [National Tax Tribunal,] the High Court or the Supreme Court.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule, ibid (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 85, for “a fee of twenty - five rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2001).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 60 (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line `7. The words in bracket shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and the Schedule (This amendment`
  line `has been struck down by the Supreme Court’s Order dated 25th September, 2014 in the Madras Bar Association Vs.`
  line `Union of India.).`
obj_root_law_sections_743_footnotes:
