  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_744_footnotes
  sourcePage 744
obj_root_law_sections_744_content:
  string
  line 744
  line `Explanation 1. — An order by the 1 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] declining to interfere`
  line `shall, for the purposes of this section, be deemed not to be an order prejudicial to the assessee.`
  line `Explanation 2. — For the purposes of this section, the 2 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] shall be`
  line `deemed to be an authority subordinate to the 1 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner].`
  line `F. — General`
  line `265. Tax tobe paid notwithstanding reference, etc. — Notwithstanding that a reference has been`
  line `made to the High Court or the Supreme Court or an appeal has been preferred to the Supreme Court, tax`
  line `shall be payable in accordance with the assessment made in the case.`
  line `266. Execution for costs awarded by Supreme Court. — The High Court may, on petition made for`
  line `the execution of the order of the Supreme Court in respect of any costs awarded thereby, transmit the`
  line `order for execution to any court subordinate to the High Court.`
  line `3 [267. Amendment of assessment on appeal. — Where as a result of an appeal under section`
  line `246 4 [or section 246A] or section 253, any change is made in the assessment of a body of individuals or`
  line `an association of persons or a new assessment of a body of individuals or an association of persons is`
  line `ordered to be made, the 5 *** Commissioner (Appeals) or the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be, shall`
  line `pass an order authorising the Assessing Officer either to amend the assessment made on any member of`
  line `the body or association or make a fresh assessment on any member of the body or association.]`
  line `268. Exclusion of time taken for copy. — In computing the period of limitation prescribed for an`
  line `appeal 6 [or an application] under this Act, the day on which the order complained of was served and, if`
  line `the assessee was not furnished with a copy of the order when the notice of the order was served upon him,`
  line `the time requisite for obtaining a copy of such order, shall be excluded.`
  line `7 [ 268A.Filing of appeal or application for reference by income-tax authority. — ( 1 ) The Board`
  line `may, from time to time, issue orders, instructions or directions to other income-tax authorities, fixing such`
  line `monetary limits as it may deem fit, for the purpose of regulating filing of appeal or application for`
  line `reference by any income-tax authority under the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line `( 2 ) Where, in pursuance of the orders, instructions or directions issued under sub-section ( 1 ), an`
  line `income-tax authority has not filed any appeal or application for reference on any issue in the case of an`
  line `assessee for any assessment year, it shall not preclude such authority from filing an appeal or application`
  line `for reference on the same issue in the case of —`
  line `( a ) the same assessee for any other assessment year; or`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 87 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 69 (w.e.f. 1-6-2000).`
  line `5. The words “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or the” omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 51 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
