  sourcePage 745
obj_root_law_sections_745_content:
  string
  line 745
  line `( b ) any other assessee for the same or any other assessment year.`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding that no appeal or application for reference has been filed by an income-tax`
  line `authority pursuant to the orders or instructions or directions issued under sub-section ( 1 ), it shall not be`
  line `lawful for an assessee, being a party in any appeal or reference, to contend that the income-tax authority`
  line `has acquiesced in the decision on the disputed issue by not filing an appeal or application for reference in`
  line `any case.`
  line `( 4 ) The Appellate Tribunal or Court, hearing such appeal or reference, shall have regard to the orders,`
  line `instructions or directions issued under sub-section ( 1 ) and the circumstances under which such appeal or`
  line `application for reference was filed or not filed in respect of any case.`
  line `( 5 ) Every order, instruction or direction which has been issued by the Board fixing monetary limits`
  line `for filing an appeal or application for reference shall be deemed to have been issued under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `and the provisions of sub-sections ( 2 ), ( 3 ) and ( 4 ) shall apply accordingly.]`
  line `269. Definition of "High Court". — In this Chapter, —`
  line `“High Court” means—`
  line `( i ) in relation to any State, the High Court for that State;`
  line `1 [( ii ) in relation to the Union territory of Delhi, the High Court of Delhi;`
  line `2 * * * * *]`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `( iv ) in relation to the Union territory of the Andaman and Nicobar Islands, the High Court at`
  line Calcutta;
  line `( v ) in relation to the Union territory of 4 [Lakshadweep], the High Court of Kerala;]`
  line `5 [( va ) in relation to the Union territory of Chandigarh, the High Court of Punjab and Haryana;`
  line `6 [( vi ) in relation to the Union territories of Dadra and Nagar Haveli and 7 *** Daman and Diu,`
  line `the High Court at Bombay; and`
  line `( vii ) in relation to the Union territory of Pondicherry, the High Court at Madras.]`
  line `1. Subs. by the Punjab Reorganisation and Delhi High Court (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) order, 1968, for clause`
  line `( ii ) (w.r.e.f. 1-11-1966).`
  line `2. Clause ( iia ) omitted by State of Himachal Pradesh (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1973 (w.r.e.f. 25-1-`
  line `1971).`
  line `3. Clause ( iii ) omitted by Act 32 of 1994, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
  line `4. Subs. by the Laccadive, Minicoy and Amindivi Islands (Alteration of Name) Adaptation of Laws Order, 1974, s. 3 and`
  line `the Schedule, for “the Laccadive, Minicoy and Amindivi Islands” (w.r.e.f. 1 -11-1973).`
  line `5. Ins. by the Punjab Reorganisation and Delhi High Court (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1968`
  line `(w.r.e.f. 1-11-1966).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 3 of 1963, s. 3(2) the Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `7. The word “Goa,” omitted by Act 32 of 994, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1995).`
