  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_746_footnotes
  sourcePage 746
obj_root_law_sections_746_content:
  string
  line 746
  line `1 [ CHAPTER XXA`
  line `A CQUISITION OF IMMOVABLE PROPERTIES IN CERTAIN CASES OF TRANSFER TO COUNTERACT EVASION OF`
  line TAX
  line `269A. Definitions. — In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) 2 [“apparent consideration”,—`
  line `( 1 ) in relation to any immovable property transferred, being immovable property of the`
  line `nature referred to in sub-clause ( i ) of clause ( e ), means, — ]`
  line `( i ) if the transfer is by way of sale, the consideration for such transfer as specified in the`
  line `instrument of transfer;`
  line `( ii ) if the transfer is by way of exchange, —`
  line `( A ) in a case where the consideration for the transfer consists of a thing or things`
  line `only, the price that such thing or things would ordinarily fetch on sale in the open market`
  line `on the date of execution of the instrument of transfer;`
  line `( B ) in a case where the consideration for the transfer consists of a thing or things and`
  line `a sum of money, the aggregate of the price that such thing or things would ordinarily`
  line `fetch on sale in the open market on the date of execution of the instrument of transfer and`
  line `such sum;`
  line `3 [( iii ) if the transfer is by way of lease, —`
  line `( A ) in a case where the consideration for the transfer consists of premium only, the`
  line `amount of premium as specified in the instrument of transfer;`
  line `( B ) in a case where the consideration for the transfer consists of rent only, the`
  line `aggregate of the moneys (if any) payable by way of rent and the amounts for the service`
  line `or things forming part of or constituting the rent, as specified in the instrument of`
  line transfer;
  line `( C ) in a case where the consideration for the transfer consists of premium and rent,`
  line `the aggregate of the amount of the premium, the moneys (if any) payable by way of rent`
  line `and the amounts for the service or things forming part of or constituting the rent, as`
  line `specified in the instrument of transfer,`
  line `and where the whole or any part of the consideration for such transfer is payable on any date or dates`
  line `falling after the date of such transfer, the value of the consideration payable after such date shall be`
  line `deemed to be the discounted value of such consideration, as on the date of such transfer, determined`
  line `by adopting the rate of interest at eight per cent per annum;`
  line `1. Chapter XXA, consisting of sections 269A to 269S, ins. by Act 45 of 1972, s. 4, (w.e.f. 15-11-1972).`
  line `2. Subs, b y Act 22 of 1981, s. 2, for “certain words” (w.e.f. 1 -7-1982).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 2, ibid, (w.e.f. 1-7-1982).`
obj_root_law_sections_746_footnotes:
