  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_747_footnotes
  sourcePage 747
obj_root_law_sections_747_content:
  string
  line 747
  line `( 2 ) in relation to any immovable property transferred, being immovable property of the nature`
  line `referred to in sub-clause ( ii ) of clause ( e ), means, —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the consideration for the transfer consists of a sum of money only,`
  line `such sum;`
  line `( ii ) in a case where the consideration for the transfer consists of a thing or things only, the`
  line `price that such thing or things would ordinarily fetch on sale in the open market on the date of`
  line `the transfer;`
  line `( iii ) in a case where the consideration for the transfer consists of a thing or things and a`
  line `sum of money, the aggregate of the price that such thing or things would ordinarily fetch on`
  line `sale in the open market on the date of the transfer and such sum,`
  line `and where the whole or any part of the consideration for such transfer is payable on any date or dates`
  line `falling after the date of such transfer, the value of the consideration payable after such date shall be`
  line `deemed to be the discounted value of such consideration, as on the date of such transfer, determined`
  line `by adopting the rate of interest at eight per cent per annum.;]`
  line `( b ) “competent authority” means 1 [a 2 [Joint] Commissioner] authorised by the Central`
  line `Government under section 269B to perform the functions of a competent authority under this`
  line Chapter;
  line `( c ) “court” means a principal civil court of original jurisdiction unless the Central Government`
  line `has appointed (as it is hereby authorised to do) any special judicial officer within any specified local`
  line `limits to perform the functions of the court under this Chapter;`
  line `3 [( d ) “fair market value”,—`
  line `( i ) in relation to any immovable property transferred by way of sale or exchange, being`
  line `immovable property of the nature referred to in sub-clause ( i ) of clause ( e ), means the price that`
  line `the immovable property would ordinarily fetch on sale in the open market on the date of`
  line `execution of the instrument of transfer of such property;`
  line `( ii ) in relation to any immovable property transferred by way of lease, being immovable`
  line `property of the nature referred to in sub-clause ( i ) of clause ( e ), means the premium that such`
  line `transfer would ordinarily fetch in the open market on the date of execution of the instrument of`
  line `transfer of such property, if the consideration for such transfer had been by way of premium only;`
  line `( iii ) in relation to any immovable property transferred, being immovable property of the`
  line `nature referred to in sub-clause ( ii ) of clause ( e ), means the consideration in the form of money`
  line `that such transfer would ordinarily fetch in the open market on the date of the transfer, if such`
  line `transfer had been made only for consideration in money;]`
  line `( e ) 4 [“immovable property” means,—`
  line `( i ) any land or any building] or part of a building, and includes, where any land or any`
  line `building or part of a building is transferred together with any machinery, plant, furniture, fittings`
  line `or other things, such machinery, plant, furniture, fittings or other things also.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 48, for “an Assistant Commissioner of Income - tax” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 3, for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 22 of 1981, s. 2, for clause ( d ) (w.e.f. 1-7-1982).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for “Immovable property means any land or any building” (w.e.f. 1 -7-1982).`
obj_root_law_sections_747_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_748:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-748
  sectionNo (748)
  orderNo 748
  title `Page 748`
  content obj_root_law_sections_748_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_748_footnotes
  sourcePage 748
obj_root_law_sections_748_content:
  string
  line 748
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this 1 [sub-clause], land, building, part of a building, machinery,`
  line `plant, furniture, fittings and other things include any rights therein;`
  line `2 [( ii ) any rights of the nature referred to in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 269AB;]`
  line `3 [( f ) “instrument of transfer” means the instrument of transfer registered under the Registration`
  line `Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), or, as the case may be, the statement registered under section 269AB with the`
  line `competent authority;]`
  line `( g ) “person interested”, in relation to any immovable property, includes all persons cla iming, or`
  line `entitled to claim, an interest in the compensation payable on account of the acquisition of that`
  line `property under this Chapter;`
  line `4 [( h ) “transfer”,—`
  line `( i ) in relation to any immovable property referred to in sub-clause ( i ) of clause ( e ), means`
  line `transfer of such property by way of sale or exchange or lease for a term of not less than twelve`
  line `years, and includes allowing the possession of such property to be taken or retained in part`
  line `performance of a contract of the nature referred to in section 53A of the Transfer of Property Act,`
  line `1882 (4 of 1882).`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-clause, a lease which provides for the extension of the`
  line `term thereof by a further term or terms shall be deemed to be a lease for a term of not less than twelve`
  line `years if the aggregate of the term for which such lease has been granted and the further term or terms for`
  line `which it can be so extended is not less than twelve years;`
  line `( ii ) in relation to any immovable property of the nature referred to in sub-clause ( ii ) of clause`
  line `( e ), means the doing of anything (whether by way of transfer of shares in a co-operative society`
  line `or company or by way of any agreement or arrangement or in any other manner whatsoever)`
  line `which has the effect of transferring, or enabling the enjoyment of, such property.]`
  line `5 [ 269AB. Registration of certain transactions. — ( 1 ) The following transactions, that is to say, —`
  line `( a ) every transaction involving the allowing of the possession of any immovable property to be`
  line `taken or retained in part performance of a contract of the nature referred to in section 53A of the`
  line `Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882), and`
  line `( b ) every transaction (whether by way of becoming a member of, or acquiring shares in, a co-`
  line `operative society, company or other association of persons or by way of any agreement or any`
  line `arrangement of whatever nature) whereby a person acquires any rights in or with respect to any`
  line `building or part of a building (whether or not including any machinery, plant, furniture, fittings or`
  line `other things therein) which has been constructed or which is to be constructed (not being a transaction`
  line `by way of sale, exchange or lease of such building or part of a building which is required to be`
  line `registered under the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908)),`
  line `shall be reduced to writing in the form of a statement by each of the parties to such transaction or by any`
  line `of the parties to such transaction acting on behalf of himself and on behalf of the other parties.`
  line `( 2 ) Every statement in respect of a transaction referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall —`
  line `( a ) be in the prescribed form;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 1981, s. 2, for “this clause” (w.e.f. 1-7-1982).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-7-1982).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for clause ( f ) (w.e.f. 1-7-1982).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 2, ibid, for clause ( h ) (w.e.f. 1-7-1982).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-7-1982).`
obj_root_law_sections_748_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_749:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-749
  sectionNo (749)
  orderNo 749
  title `Page 749`
  content obj_root_law_sections_749_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_749_footnotes
  sourcePage 749
obj_root_law_sections_749_content:
  string
  line 749
  line `( b ) set forth such particulars as may be prescribed; and`
  line `( c ) be verified in the prescribed manner,`
  line `and registered with the competent authority, in such manner and within such time as may be prescribed,`
  line `by each of the parties to such transaction or by any of the parties to such transaction acting on behalf of`
  line `himself and on behalf of the other parties.]`
  line `269B.Competent authority. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may, by general or special order`
  line `published in the Official Gazette,`
  line `( a ) authorise as many 1 [ 2 [Joint Commissioners], as it thinks fit, to perform the functions of a`
  line `competent authority under this Chapter; and`
  line `( b ) define the local limits within which the competent authorities shall perform their functions`
  line `under this Chapter.`
  line `( 2 ) In respect of any function to be performed by a competent authority under any provision of this`
  line `Chapter in relation to any immovable property referred to in section 269C, the competent authority`
  line `referred to therein shall, —`
  line `( a ) in a case where such property is situate within the local limits of the jurisdiction of only one`
  line `competent authority, be such competent authority;`
  line `( b ) in a case where such property is situate within the local limits of the jurisdiction of two or`
  line `more competent authorities, be the competent authority empowered to perform such functions in`
  line `relation to such property in accordance with rules made in this behalf by the Board under section 295.`
  line `3 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, immovable property, being rights of the nature`
  line `referred to in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 269AB in, or with respect to, any building or part of`
  line `a building which has been constructed or which is to be constructed shall be deemed to be situate at the`
  line `place where the building has been constructed or is to be constructed.]`
  line `( 3 ) No person shall be entitled to call in question the jurisdiction of a competent authority in respect`
  line `of any immovable property after the expiry of thirty days from the date on which such competent`
  line `authority initiates proceedings under section 269D for the acquisition of such property.`
  line `( 4 ) Subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 3 ), where the jurisdiction of a competent authority is`
  line `questioned, the competent authority shall, if satisfied with the correctness of the claim, by order in`
  line `writing, determine the question accordingly and if he is not so satisfied, he shall refer the question to the`
  line `Board and the Board shall, by order in writing, determine the question.`
  line `269C. Immovable property in respect of which proceedings for acquisition may be taken. — ( 1 )`
  line `Where the competent authority has reason to believe that any immovable property of a fair market value`
  line `exceeding 4 [one hundred thousand rupees] has been transferred by a person (hereafter in this Chapter`
  line `referred to as the transferor) to another person (hereafter in this Chapter referred to as the transferee) for`
  line `an apparent consideration which is less than the fair market value of the property and that the`
  line `consideration for such transfer as agreed to between the parties has not been truly stated in the instrument`
  line `of transfer with the object of —`
  line `( a ) facilitating the reduction or evasion of the liability of the transferor to pay tax under this Act`
  line `in respect of any income arising from the transfer; or`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 49, fo r “Assistant Commissioners of Income - tax” (w.r.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 3, for “Deputy Commissioners” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 22 of 1981, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-7-1982).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 25, for “twenty -five thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_749_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_750:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-750
  sectionNo (750)
  orderNo 750
  title `Page 750`
  content obj_root_law_sections_750_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_750_footnotes
  sourcePage 750
obj_root_law_sections_750_content:
  string
  line 750
  line `( b ) facilitating the concealment of any income or any moneys or other assets which have not been`
  line `or which ought to be disclosed by the transferee for the purposes of the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922`
  line `(11 of 1922), or this Act or the Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957),`
  line `the competent authority may, subject to the provisions of this Chapter, initiate proceedings for the`
  line `acquisition of such property under this Chapter:`
  line `Provided that before initiating such proceedings, the competent authority shall record his reasons for`
  line `doing so:`
  line `Provided further that no such proceedings shall be initiated unless the competent authority has reason`
  line `to believe that the fair market value of the property exceeds the apparent consideration therefor by more`
  line `than fifteen per cent of such apparent consideration.`
  line `( 2 ) In any proceedings under this Chapter in respect of any immovable property, —`
  line `( a ) where the fair market value of such property exceeds the apparent consideration therefor by`
  line `more than twenty-five per cent of such apparent consideration, it shall be conclusive proof that the`
  line `consideration for such transfer as agreed to between the parties has not been truly stated in the`
  line `instrument of transfer;`
  line `( b ) where the property has been transferred for an apparent consideration which is less than its`
  line `fair market value, it shall be presumed, unless the contrary is proved, that the consideration for such`
  line `transfer as agreed to between the parties has not been truly stated in the instrument of transfer with`
  line `such object as is referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `269D. Preliminary notice. — ( 1 ) The competent authority shall initiate proceedings for the`
  line `acquisition, under this Chapter, of any immovable property referred to in section 269C by notice to that`
  line `effect published in the Official Gazette:`
  line `Provided that no such proceedings shall be initiated in respect of any immovable property after the`
  line `expiration of a period of 1 [nine months] from the end of the month in which the instrument of transfer in`
  line `respect of such property is registered under the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), 2 [or, as the case may`
  line `be, section 269AB]:`
  line `Provided further that —`
  line `( a ) in a case where it is determined under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 269B by the competent`
  line `authority who has initiated proceedings for the acquisition of any immovable property under this`
  line `Chapter or by the Board that such competent authority has no jurisdiction to initiate such proceedings,`
  line `the competent authority having jurisdiction may initiate such proceedings within —`
  line `( i ) the period of 1 [nine months] specified in the foregoing proviso; or`
  line `( ii ) a period of thirty days from the date of such determination,`
  line `whichever period expires later;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 66 of 1973, s. 2, for “six month” (w.r.e.f. 15 -11-1972).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 22 of 1981, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-7-1982).`
obj_root_law_sections_750_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_751:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-751
  sectionNo (751)
  orderNo 751
  title `Page 751`
  content obj_root_law_sections_751_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_751_footnotes
  sourcePage 751
obj_root_law_sections_751_content:
  string
  line 751
  line `( b ) in a case where proceedings for the acquisition of any immovable property under this Chapter`
  line `could not be initiated during any period of time by reason of any injunction or order of any court`
  line `prohibiting the initiation of such proceedings or preventing the examination of documents or other`
  line `materials required to be examined for the purpose of determining whether such proceedings should be`
  line `initiated, the time of the continuance of the injunction or order, the day on which it was issued or`
  line `made and the day on which it was withdrawn shall be excluded in computing the period during which`
  line `such proceedings may be initiated under this sub-section.`
  line `( 2 ) The competent authority shall —`
  line `( a ) cause a notice under sub-section (1) in respect of any immovable property to be served on the`
  line `transferor, the transferee, the person in occupation of the property, if the transferee is not in`
  line `occupation thereof, and on every person whom the competent authority knows to be interested in the`
  line property;
  line `( b ) cause such notice to be published —`
  line `( i ) in his office by affixing a copy thereof to a conspicuous place;`
  line `( ii ) in the locality in which the immovable property to which it relates is situate, by affixing a`
  line `copy thereof to a conspicuous part of the property and also by making known in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed the substance of such notice at convenient places in the said locality.`
  line `1 [ Explanation. — The provisions of the Explanation to sub-section (2) of section 269B shall apply for`
  line `the purposes of this sub-section as they apply for the purposes of that sub-section.]`
  line `269E. Objections. — ( 1 ) Objections against the acquisition of the immovable property in respect of`
  line `which a notice has been published in the Official Gazette under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 269D may be`
  line `made —`
  line `( a ) by the transferor or the transferee or any other person referred to in clause ( a ) of sub-section`
  line `( 2 ) of that section, within a period of forty-five days from the date of such publication or a period of`
  line `thirty days from the date of service of notice on such person under the said clause, whichever period`
  line `expires later;`
  line `( b ) by any other person interested in such immovable property, within forty-five days from the`
  line `date of such publication.`
  line `( 2 ) Every objection under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be made to the competent authority in writing.`
  line `( 3 ) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that objection may be made under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `that the provisions of clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 269C do not apply in relation to any`
  line `immovable property on the ground that the fair market value of such property does not exceed the`
  line `apparent consideration therefor by more than twenty-five per cent of such apparent consideration.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 1981, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-7-1982).`
obj_root_law_sections_751_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_752:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-752
  sectionNo (752)
  orderNo 752
  title `Page 752`
  content obj_root_law_sections_752_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_752_footnotes
  sourcePage 752
obj_root_law_sections_752_content:
  string
  line 752
  line `269F. Hearing of objections. — ( 1 ) The competent authority shall fix a day and place for the hearing`
  line `of the objections made under section 269E against the acquisition under this Chapter of any immovable`
  line `property, and shall give notice of the same to every person who has made such objection:`
  line `Provided that such notice shall also be given to the transferee of such property even if he has not`
  line `made any such objection.`
  line `( 2 ) Every person to whom a notice is given under sub-section ( 1 ) shall have the right to be heard at`
  line `the hearing of the objections.`
  line `( 3 ) The competent authority shall have the power to adjourn the hearing of the objections from time`
  line `to time.`
  line `( 4 ) The competent authority may, before disposing of the objections, make such further inquiry as he`
  line `thinks fit.`
  line `( 5 ) The decision of the competent authority in respect of the objections heard shall be in writing and`
  line `shall state the reasons for the decision with respect to each objection.`
  line `( 6 ) If after hearing the objections, if any, and after taking into account all the relevant material on`
  line `record, the competent authority is satisfied that, —`
  line `( a ) the immovable property to which the proceedings relate is of a fair market value exceeding`
  line `1 [one hundred thousand rupees];`
  line `( b ) the fair market value of such property exceeds the apparent consideration therefor by more`
  line `than fifteen per cent of such apparent consideration; and`
  line `( c ) the consideration for such transfer as agreed to between the parties has not been truly stated in`
  line `the instrument of transfer with such object as is referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) of section 269C,`
  line `he may, after obtaining the approval of the 2 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner], make an order`
  line `for the acquisition of the property under this Chapter.`
  line `Explanation. — In this sub-section, 2 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner], in relation to a`
  line `competent authority, means such 2 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] as the Board may, by`
  line `general or special order in writing, specify in this behalf.`
  line `( 7 ) If the competent authority is not satisfied as provided in sub-section ( 6 ), he shall, by order in`
  line `writing, declare that the property will not be acquired under this Chapter.`
  line `( 8 ) The competent authority shall serve a copy of his order under sub-section ( 6 ) or sub-section ( 7 ), as`
  line `the case may be, on the transferor, the transferee and on every person who has made objections against`
  line `such acquisition under section 269E.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 26, for “twenty -five thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1984).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_752_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_753:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-753
  sectionNo (753)
  orderNo 753
  title `Page 753`
  content obj_root_law_sections_753_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_753_footnotes
  sourcePage 753
obj_root_law_sections_753_content:
  string
  line 753
  line `( 9 ) In any proceedings under this Chapter in respect of any immovable property, no objection shall be`
  line `entertained on the ground that although the apparent consideration for the property is less than the fair`
  line `market value of the property on the 1 [date of the execution of the instrument of transfer or where such`
  line `property is of the nature referred to in sub-clause ( ii ) of clause ( e ) of section 269A on the date of the`
  line `transfer], the consideration as agreed to between the parties has been truly stated in the instrument of`
  line `transfer because such consideration was agreed to having regard to the price that such property would`
  line `have ordinarily fetched 2 [on such transfer in the open market on the date of the conclusion of the`
  line `agreement to transfer the property], except where such agreement has been registered under the`
  line `Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908).`
  line `269G. Appeal against order for acquisition. — ( 1 ) An appeal may be preferred to the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal against the order for the acquisition of any immovable property made by the competent authority`
  line `under section 269F, —`
  line `( a ) by the transferor or the transferee or any other person referred to in sub-section ( 8 ) of that`
  line `section, within a period of forty-five days from the date of such order or a period of thirty days from`
  line `the date of service of a copy of the order on such person under the said sub-section, whichever period`
  line `expires later;`
  line `( b ) by any other person interested in such immovable property, within forty-five days from the`
  line `date of such order:`
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may, on an application made in this behalf before the expiry of`
  line `the said period of forty-five days or, as the case may be, thirty days, permit, by order, the appeal to be`
  line `presented within such further period as may be specified therein if the applicant satisfies the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal that he has sufficient cause for not being able to present the appeal within the said period of`
  line `forty-five days or, as the case may be, thirty days.`
  line `( 2 ) Every appeal under this section shall be in the prescribed form and shall be verified in the`
  line `prescribed manner and shall be accompanied by a fee of 3 [two hundred rupees].`
  line `( 3 ) The Appellate Tribunal shall fix a day and place for the hearing of the appeal and shall give notice`
  line `of the same to the appellant and to the competent authority.`
  line `( 4 ) The Appellate Tribunal may, after giving the appellant and the competent authority an opportunity`
  line `of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit.`
  line `( 5 ) The Appellate Tribunal may, at any time within thirty days from the date of the order, with a view`
  line `to rectifying any mistake apparent from the record, amend any order passed by it under sub-section ( 4 )`
  line `and shall make such amendment if the mistake is brought to its notice by the appellant or the competent`
  line `authority:`
  line `Provided that if any such amendment is likely to affect any person prejudicially, it shall not be made`
  line `without giving to such person a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line `( 6 ) The Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of any orders passed under this section to the appellant`
  line `and to the 4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner].`
  line `( 7 ) Save as provided in section 269H, orders passed by the Appellate Tribunal on appeal shall be`
  line final.
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 1981, s. 6, for “date of execution of the instrument of transfer” (w.e.f. 1 -7-1982).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for “on sale in the open market on the date of the conclusion of the agreement to sell the property”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-7-1982).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 16 of 1981, s. 21, for “one hundred and twenty - five rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1981).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_753_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_754:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-754
  sectionNo (754)
  orderNo 754
  title `Page 754`
  content obj_root_law_sections_754_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_754_footnotes
  sourcePage 754
obj_root_law_sections_754_content:
  string
  line 754
  line `( 8 ) Every appeal under this section shall be disposed of as expeditiously as possible and endeavour`
  line `shall be made to dispose of every such appeal within ninety days from the date on which it is presented.`
  line `( 9 ) The provisions of section 255 (except sub-section ( 3 ) thereof) shall, so far as may be, apply in`
  line `relation to the powers, functions and proceedings of the Appellate Tribunal under this section as they`
  line `apply in relation to the powers, functions and proceedings of the Appellate Tribunal under Chapter XX.`
  line `269H. Appeal to High Court. — ( 1 ) The 1 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] or any person`
  line `aggrieved by any order of the Appellate Tribunal under section 269G may, within sixty days of the date`
  line `on which he is served with notice of such order under that section, prefer an appeal against such order to`
  line `the High Court on any question of law:`
  line `Provided that the High Court may, on an application made in this behalf before the expiry of the said`
  line `period of sixty days, permit, by order, the appeal to be presented within such further period as may be`
  line `specified therein, if the applicant satisfies the High Court that he has sufficient cause for not being able to`
  line `present the appeal within the said period of sixty days.`
  line `( 2 ) An appeal under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be heard by a Bench of not less than two Judges of the High`
  line `Court and the provisions of section 259 shall apply in relation to any such appeal as they apply in relation`
  line `to a case referred to the High Court under section 256.`
  line `( 3 ) The costs of the appeal shall be in the discretion of the High Court.`
  line `269-I. Vesting of property in Central Government. — ( 1 ) As soon as may be after the order for`
  line `acquisition of any immovable property made undersub-section ( 6 ) of section 269F becomes final, the`
  line `competent authority may, by notice in writing, order any person who may be in possession of the`
  line `immovable property to surrender or deliver possession thereof to the competent authority or any other`
  line `person duly authorised in writing by the competent authority in this behalf, within thirty days of the date`
  line `of the service of the notice.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, an order for the acquisition of any immovable`
  line `property (hereafter in this Explanation referred to as the order for acquisition) made under sub-section ( 6 )`
  line `of section 269F becomes final, —`
  line `( a ) in a case where the order for acquisition is not made the subject of an appeal to the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal under section 269G, upon the expiry of the period during which such appeal may be`
  line `presented under that section;`
  line `( b ) in a case where the order for acquisition is made the subject of an appeal to the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal under section 269G, —`
  line `( i ) if the order for acquisition is confirmed by the Appellate Tribunal and the order of the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal is not made the subject of an appeal to the High Court under section 269H,`
  line `upon the expiry of the period during which such appeal may be presented under that section to the`
  line `High Court;`
  line `( ii ) if the order of the Appellate Tribunal is made the subject of an appeal to the High Court`
  line `under section 269H, upon the confirmation of the order for acquisition by the High Court.`
  line `( 2 ) If any person refuses or fails to comply with the notice under sub-section ( 1 ), the competent`
  line `authority or other person duly authorised by the competent authority under that sub-section may take`
  line `possession of the immovable property and may, for that purpose, use such force as may be necessary.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_754_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_755:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-755
  sectionNo (755)
  orderNo 755
  title `Page 755`
  content obj_root_law_sections_755_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_755_footnotes
  sourcePage 755
obj_root_law_sections_755_content:
  string
  line 755
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 2 ), the competent authority may, for the`
  line `purpose of taking possession of any property referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), requisition the services of any`
  line `police officer to assist him and it shall be the duty of such officer to comply with such requisition.`
  line `( 4 ) When the possession of the immovable property is surrendered or delivered under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `to the competent authority or a person duly authorised by him in that behalf or, as the case may be, when`
  line `the possession thereof is taken under sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-section ( 3 ) by such authority or person, the`
  line `property shall vest absolutely in the Central Government free from all encumbrances:`
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall operate to discharge the transferee or any other person`
  line `(not being the Central Government) from liability in respect of such encumbrances and, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in any other law, such liability may be enforced against the transferee or such other`
  line `person by a suit for damages.`
  line `1 [( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 4 ) or any other law or any instrument or any`
  line `agreement for the time being in force, where an order for acquisition of any immovable property, being`
  line `rights of the nature referred to in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 269AB, in or with respect to any`
  line `building or part of a building which has been constructed or which is to be constructed, has become final,`
  line `then, such order shall, by its own force, have the effect of —`
  line `( a ) vesting such rights in the Central Government, and`
  line `( b ) placing the Central Government in the same position in relation to such rights as the person in`
  line `whom such rights would have continued to vest if such order had not become final,`
  line `and the competent authority may issue such directions as he may deem fit to any person concerned for`
  line `taking the necessary steps for compliance with the provisions of clauses ( a ) and ( b ).]`
  line `( 6 ) In the case of any immovable property, being rights of the nature referred to in clause ( b ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 269AB, in or with respect to any building or part of a building, the provisions of`
  line `sub-sections ( 1 ), ( 2 ) and ( 3 ) shall have effect as if the references to immovable property therein were a`
  line `reference to such building or, as the case may be, part of such building.]`
  line `269J. Compensation. — ( 1 ) Where any immovable property is acquired under this Chapter, the`
  line `Central Government shall pay for such acquisition compensation which shall be a sum equal to the`
  line `aggregate of the amount of the apparent consideration for its transfer and fifteen per cent of the said`
  line `amount:`
  line `2 [Provided that in a case where, under the agreement between the parties concerned, the whole or any`
  line `part of the consideration for the transfer of such immovable property is payable on any date or dates`
  line `falling after the date on which such property is acquired, the compensation payable by the Central`
  line `Government shall be the aggregate of the following amounts, namely: —`
  line `( i ) an amount equal to fifteen per cent of the apparent consideration;`
  line `( ii ) the amount, if any, that has become payable in accordance with such agreement on or before`
  line `the date on which such property is acquired under this Chapter; and`
  line `( iii ) the amount payable after the date on which such property is acquired under this Chapter.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 1981, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-7-1982).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 8 ibid. (w.e.f. 1-7-1982).`
obj_root_law_sections_755_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_756:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-756
  sectionNo (756)
  orderNo 756
  title `Page 756`
  content obj_root_law_sections_756_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_756_footnotes
  sourcePage 756
obj_root_law_sections_756_content:
  string
  line 756
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), —`
  line `( a ) where, after the transfer to the transferee of the property referred to in that sub-section but`
  line `before the vesting of the property in the Central Government, the property has been damaged`
  line `(otherwise than as a result of normal wear and tear), the compensation payable under that sub-section`
  line `shall be reduced by such amount as the competent authority and the persons entitled to the`
  line `compensation may agree within fifteen days of the vesting of the property in the Central Government`
  line `or in default of such agreement as the court may, on a reference made to it in this behalf by the`
  line `competent authority or by any person duly authorised for the purpose by the competent authority,`
  line `determine to be the amount that may have to be expended for restoring the property to the condition`
  line `in which it was at the time of such transfer;`
  line `( b ) where, after the transfer of such property to the transferee but before the date of publication`
  line `in the Official Gazette of the notice in respect of such property under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 269D,`
  line `any improvements have been made to the property, whether by way of addition or alteration or in any`
  line `other manner, the compensation payable in respect of such property under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be`
  line `increased by such amount as the competent authority and the persons entitled to the compensation`
  line `may agree within fifteen days of the vesting of the property in the Central Government or in default`
  line `of such agreement as the court may, on a reference made to it in this behalf by the competent`
  line `authority or by any person duly authorised for the purpose by the competent authority, determine to`
  line `be the amount spent for making such improvements.`
  line `( 3 ) Every reference under clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 2 ) shall be made within thirty days`
  line `of the date on which the immovable property to which it relates becomes vested in the Central`
  line `Government or within such further period as the court may, on an application made in this behalf before`
  line `the expiry of the said period and on being satisfied that there is sufficient cause for doing so, allow and`
  line `such reference shall state clearly the compensation payable under sub-section ( 1 ) in respect of the`
  line `immovable property and the amount by which, according to the estimate of the competent authority, such`
  line `compensation shall be reduced under clause ( a ) or, as the case may be, increased under clause ( b ), of`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ).`
  line `( 4 ) The amount by which the compensation payable under sub-section ( 1 ) in respect of any`
  line `immovable property acquired under this Chapter falls short of the amount which would have been`
  line `payable as compensation if that property had been acquired under the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of`
  line `1894), after the issue of a preliminary notice under section 4 of that Act on the date of publication in the`
  line `Official Gazette of the notice in respect of the property under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 269D, shall be`
  line `deemed to have been realised by the Central Government as a penalty from the transferee for being a`
  line `party to a transfer with such object as is referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 269C, and no penalty shall be levied for any assessment year on the transferee —`
  line `( a ) under clause ( iii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 271, for concealing the particulars or furnishing`
  line `inaccurate particulars of so much of his income as is utilised by him for paying to the transferor, by`
  line `way of consideration for the property, any amount in excess of the apparent consideration for the`
  line `property, notwithstanding that such amount is included in the income of the transferee;`
  line `( b ) under clause ( iii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 18 of the Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957),`
  line `for concealing the particulars or furnishing inaccurate particulars of so much of his assets as are`
  line `utilised by him for paying to the transferor, by way of consideration for the property, any amount in`
  line `excess of the apparent consideration for the property, notwithstanding that such assets are included in`
  line `the net wealth of the transferee.`
  line `269K. Payment or deposit of compensation. — ( 1 ) The amount of compensation payable in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of section 269J for the acquisition of any immovable property shall be`
  line `tendered to the person or persons entitled thereto, as soon as may be, after the property becomes vested in`
  line `the Central Government under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 269-I:`
obj_root_law_sections_756_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_757:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-757
  sectionNo (757)
  orderNo 757
  title `Page 757`
  content obj_root_law_sections_757_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_757_footnotes
  sourcePage 757
obj_root_law_sections_757_content:
  string
  line 757
  line `1 [Provided that in a case falling under the proviso to sub-section ( 1 ) of section 269J, the amounts`
  line `referred to in clause ( i ) and clause ( ii ) of that proviso shall be tendered to the person or persons entitled`
  line `thereto, as soon as may be, after the property becomes vested in the Central Government under section`
  line `269-I, and the amount referred to in clause ( iii ) of the said proviso shall be tendered on the date on which`
  line `it would be payable in accordance with the agreement between the parties concerned, and where such`
  line `amount is payable in instalments on different dates, then in such instalments on those dates:`
  line `Provided further that] in any case where a reference is or has to be made under sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 269J to the court for the determination of the amount by which the compensation payable under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of that section shall be reduced or increased, the amount of such compensation as reduced`
  line `or increased by the amount estimated in that behalf by the competent authority for the purposes of such`
  line `reference shall be tendered as aforesaid.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), if any dispute arises as to the`
  line `apportionment of the compensation amongst persons claiming to be entitled thereto, the Central`
  line `Government shall deposit in the court the compensation required to be tendered under sub-section ( 1 ) and`
  line `refer such dispute for the decision of the court and the decision of the court thereon shall be final.`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), if the persons entitled to compensation do`
  line `not consent to receive it, or if there is no person competent to alienate the immovable property, or if there`
  line `is any dispute as to the title to receive the compensation, the Central Government shall deposit in the`
  line `court the compensation required to be tendered under sub-section ( 1 ) and refer the matter for the decision`
  line `of the court:`
  line `Provided that nothing herein contained shall affect the liability of any person who may receive the`
  line `whole or any part of the compensation for any immovable property acquired under this Chapter to pay the`
  line `same to the person lawfully entitled thereto.`
  line `( 4 ) If the Central Government fails to tender under sub-section ( 1 ) or deposit under sub-section ( 2 ) or`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ) the whole or any part of the compensation required to be tendered or deposited thereunder`
  line `within thirty days of the date on which the immovable property to which the compensation relates`
  line `becomes vested in the Central Government under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 269-I, the Central`
  line `Government shall be liable to pay simple interest at the rate of 2 [fifteen per cent per.] annum reckoned`
  line `from the day immediately following the date of expiry of the said period up to the date on which it so`
  line `tenders or deposits such compensation or, as the case may be, such part of the compensation.`
  line `( 5 ) Where any amount of compensation (including interest, if any, thereon) has been deposited in the`
  line `court under this section, the court may, either of its own motion or on an application made by or on behalf`
  line `of any party interested or claiming to be interested in such amount, order the same to be invested in such`
  line `Government or other securities as it may think proper, and may direct the interest or other proceeds of any`
  line `such investment to be accumulated and paid in such manner as will, in its opinion, give the parties`
  line `interested therein the same benefit therefrom as they might have had from the immovable property in`
  line `respect whereof such amount has been deposited or as near thereto as may be.`
  line `269L. Assistance by Valuation Officers. — ( 1 ) The competent authority may, —`
  line `( a ) for the purpose of initiating proceedings for the acquisition of any immovable property`
  line `under section 269C or for the purpose of making an order under section 269F in respect of any`
  line `immovable property, require a Valuation Officer to determine the fair market value of such property`
  line `and report the same to him;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 1981, s. 9, for “Provided that” (w.e.f. 1 -7-1982).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 24, for “twelve per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_757_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_758:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-758
  sectionNo (758)
  orderNo 758
  title `Page 758`
  content obj_root_law_sections_758_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_758_footnotes
  sourcePage 758
obj_root_law_sections_758_content:
  string
  line 758
  line `( b ) for the purpose of estimating the amount by which the compensation payable under sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ) of section 269J in respect of any immovable property may be reduced or, as the case may`
  line `be, increased under clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of that section, require the Valuation`
  line `Officer to make such estimate and report the same to him.`
  line `( 2 ) The Valuation Officer to whom a reference is made under clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) shall, for the purpose of dealing with such reference, have all the powers that he has under section`
  line `38A of the Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957).`
  line `( 3 ) If in an appeal under section 269G against the order for acquisition of any immovable property,`
  line `the fair market value of such property is in dispute, the Appellate Tribunal shall, on a request being made`
  line `in this behalf by the competent authority, give an opportunity of being heard to any Valuation Officer`
  line `nominated for the purpose by the competent authority.`
  line `Explanation. —In this section, “Valuation Officer” has the same meaning as in clause ( r ) of section 2`
  line `of the Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957).`
  line `269M. Powers of competent authority. — The competent authority shall have, for the purposes of`
  line `this Chapter, all the powers that a 1 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] has, for the purposes of`
  line `this Act, under section 131.`
  line `269N. Rectification of mistakes. — With a view to rectifying any mistake apparent from the record,`
  line `the competent authority may amend any order made by him under this Chapter at any time before the`
  line `time for presenting an appeal against such order has expired, either on his own motion or on the mistake`
  line `being brought to his notice by any person affected by the order:`
  line `Provided that if any such amendment is likely to affect any person prejudicially, it shall not be made`
  line `without giving to such person a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line `269-O. Appearance by authorised representative or registered valuer. — Any person who is`
  line `entitled or required to attend before a competent authority or the Appellate Tribunal in any proceeding`
  line `under this Chapter, otherwise than when required to attend personally for examination on oath or`
  line `affirmation, may attend —`
  line `( a ) by an authorised representative in connection with any matter;`
  line `( b ) by a registered valuer in connection with any matter relating to the valuation of any`
  line `immovable property for the purposes of this Chapter or the estimation of the amount by which the`
  line `compensation payable under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 269J for the acquisition of any immovable`
  line `property may be reduced or, as the case may be, increased in accordance with the provisions of clause`
  line `( a ) or clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of that section.`
  line `Explanation. — In this section, —`
  line `( i ) “authorised representative” has the ( b ) by a registered valuer in connection with any matter`
  line `relating to the valuation of any immovable property for the purposes of this Chapter or the estimation`
  line `of the amount by which the compensation payable under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 269J for the`
  line `acquisition of any immovable property may be reduced or, as the case may be, increased in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of that section.`
  line `Explanation. — In this section, —`
  line `( i ) “authorised representative” has the same meaning as in section 288;`
  line `( ii ) “registered valuer” has the same meani ng as in clause ( oaa ) of section 2 of the Wealth-tax`
  line `Act, 1957 (27 of 1957).`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_758_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_759:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-759
  sectionNo (759)
  orderNo 759
  title `Page 759`
  content obj_root_law_sections_759_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_759_footnotes
  sourcePage 759
obj_root_law_sections_759_content:
  string
  line 759
  line `269P. Statement to be furnished in respect of transfers of immovable property. — ( 1 )`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, no registering officer`
  line `appointed under the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), shall register any document which purports to`
  line `transfer any immovable property belonging to any person unless a statement in duplicate in respect of`
  line `such transfer, in the prescribed form and verified in the prescribed manner and setting forth such`
  line `particulars as may be prescribed, is furnished to him along with the instrument of transfer:`
  line `1 [Provided that the provisions of this sub-section shall not apply in relation to any document which`
  line `purports to transfer any immovable property for an apparent consideration not exceeding 2 [fifty thousand`
  line rupees].
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this prov iso, “apparent consideration” shall have the meaning`
  line `assigned to it in clause ( a ) of section 269A subject to the modifications that for the expressions`
  line `“immovable property transferred” and “instrument of transfer” occurring in that clause, the expressions`
  line `“immovable property purported to be transferred” and “document purporting to transfer such immovable`
  line `property” shall, respectively, be substituted.]`
  line `( 2 ) The registering officer shall, at the end of every fortnight, forward to the competent authority, —`
  line `( a ) one set of the statements received by him under sub-section ( 1 ) during the fortnight; and`
  line `( b ) a return in the prescribed form and verified in the prescribed manner and setting forth such`
  line `particulars as may be prescribed in respect of documents of the nature referred to in sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `which have been registered by him during the fortnight.`
  line `269Q. Chapter not to apply to transfers to relatives. — The provisions of this Chapter shall not`
  line `apply to or in relation to any transfer of immovable property made by a person to his relative on account`
  line `of natural love and affection for a consideration which is less than its fair market value if a recital to that`
  line `effect is made in the instrument of transfer.`
  line `269R. Properties liable for acquisition under this Chapter not to be acquired under other`
  line `laws. — Notwithstanding anything contained in the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894), or any`
  line `corresponding law for the time being in force, no immovable property referred to in section 269C shall be`
  line `acquired for any purpose of the Union under that Act or such law unless the time for initiation of`
  line `proceedings for the acquisition of such property under this Chapter has expired without such proceedings`
  line `having been initiated or unless the competent authority has declared that such property will not be`
  line `acquired under this Chapter.`
  line `3 [ 269RR. Chapter not to apply where transfer of immovable property made after a certain`
  line `date. — The provisions of this Chapter shall not apply to or in relation to the transfer of any immovable`
  line `property made after the 30th day of September, 1986.]`
  line `269S. Chapter not to extend to State of Jammu and Kashmir. — The provisions of this Chapter`
  line `shall not extend to the State of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 66 of 1973, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-1-1974).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 27, for “ten thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1984).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 1986, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-10-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_759_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_760:
