  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_762_footnotes
  sourcePage 762
obj_root_law_sections_762_content:
  string
  line 762
  line `is twenty thousand rupees or more:`
  line `Provided that where the repayment is by a branch of a banking company or co-operative bank, such`
  line `repayment may also be made by crediting the amount of such loan or deposit to the savings bank account`
  line `or the current account (if any) with such branch of the person to whom such loan or deposit has to be`
  line `repaid:`
  line `1 [Provided further that nothing contained in this section shall apply to repayment of any loan or`
  line `deposit 2 [or specified advance] taken or accepted from —`
  line `( i ) Government;`
  line `( ii ) any banking company, post office savings bank or co-operative bank;`
  line `( iii ) any corporation established by a Central, State or Provincial Act;`
  line `( iv ) any Government companyas defined in section 617 of the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956);`
  line `( v ) such other institution, association or body or class of institutions, associations or bodies which`
  line `the Central Government may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, notify in this behalf in the`
  line `Official Gazette.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “banking company” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( i ) of`
  line `the Explanation to section 269SS;`
  line `( ii ) “co - operative bank” shall have the meaning assigned to it in Part V of the Banking Regulation`
  line `Act, 1949 (10 of 1949);`
  line `( iii ) “loan or deposit” mean s any loan or deposit of money which is repayable after notice or`
  line `repayable after a period and, in the case of a person other than a company, includes loan or deposit of`
  line `any nature;]]`
  line `2 [( iv ) “specified advance” means any sum of money in the nature of advan ce, by whatever name`
  line `called, in relation to transfer of an immovable property, whether or not the transfer takes place.]`
  line `3 [ 269TT.Mode of repayment of Special Bearer Bonds, 1991. — Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other law for the time being in force, the amount payable on redemption of Special`
  line `Bearer Bonds, 1991, shall be paid only by an account payee cheque or account payee bank draft drawn in`
  line `the name of the person to whom such payment is to be made.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 94 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 69 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 38 of 1981, s. 3 (w.e.f. 19-9-1981).`
obj_root_law_sections_762_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_763:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-763
  sectionNo (763)
  orderNo 763
  title `Page 763`
  content obj_root_law_sections_763_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_763_footnotes
  sourcePage 763
obj_root_law_sections_763_content:
  string
  line 763
  line `1 [CHAPTER XXC`
  line `P URCHASE BY CENTRAL GOVERNMENT OF IMMOVABLE PROPERTIES IN CERTAIN CASES OF TRANSFER`
  line `269U. Commencement of Chapter. — The provisions of this Chapter shall come into force on such`
  line `date as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint, and different dates`
  line `may be appointed for different areas.`
  line `269UA. Definitions. — In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “agreement for transfer” means an agreement, whether registered under the Registration Act,`
  line `1908 (16 of 1908) or not, for the transfer of any immovable property;`
  line `( b ) “apparent consideration”,—`
  line `( 1 ) in relation to any immovable property in respect of which an agreement for transfer is`
  line `made, being immovable property of the nature referred to in sub-clause ( i ) of clause ( d ), means, —`
  line `( i ) if the immovable property is to be transferred by way of sale, the consideration for`
  line `such transfer as specified in the agreement for transfer;`
  line `( ii ) if the immovable property is to be transferred by way of exchange, —`
  line `( A ) in a case where the consideration for the transfer consists of a thing or things`
  line `only, the price that such thing or things would ordinarily fetch on sale in the open market`
  line `on the date on which the agreement for transfer is made;`
  line `( B ) in a case where the consideration for the transfer consists of a thing or things and`
  line `a sum of money, the aggregate of the price that such thing or things would ordinarily`
  line `fetch on sale in the open market on the date on which the agreement for transfer is made,`
  line `and such sum;`
  line `( iii ) if the immovable property is to be transferred by way of lease, —`
  line `( A ) in a case where the consideration for the transfer consists of premium only, the`
  line `amount of premium as specified in the agreement for transfer;`
  line `( B ) in a case where the consideration for the transfer consists of rent only, the`
  line `aggregate of the moneys (if any) payable by way of rent and the amounts for the service`
  line `or things forming part of or constituting the rent, as specified in the agreement for`
  line transfer;
  line `( C ) in a case where the consideration for the transfer consists of premium and rent,`
  line `the aggregate of the amount of the premium, the moneys (if any) payable by way of rent`
  line `and the amounts for the service or things forming part of or constituting the rent, as`
  line `specified in the agreement for transfer,`
  line `and where the whole or any part of the consideration for such transfer is payable on any date or`
  line `dates falling after the date of such agreement for transfer, the value of the consideration payable`
  line `after such date shall be deemed to be the discounted value of such consideration, as on the date of`
  line `such agreement for transfer, determined by adopting such rate of interest as may be prescribed in`
  line `this behalf;`
  line `( 2 ) in relation to any immovable property in respect of which an agreement for transfer is`
  line `made, being immovable property of the nature referred to in sub-clause ( ii ) of clause ( d ),`
  line `means, —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the consideration for the transfer consists of a sum of money only,`
  line `such sum;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 1986, s. 34 (w.e.f. 13-5-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_763_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_764:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-764
  sectionNo (764)
  orderNo 764
  title `Page 764`
  content obj_root_law_sections_764_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_764_footnotes
  sourcePage 764
obj_root_law_sections_764_content:
  string
  line 764
  line `( ii ) in a case where the consideration for the transfer consists of a thing or things only, the`
  line `price that such thing or things would ordinarily fetch on sale in the open market on the date`
  line `on which the agreement for transfer is made;`
  line `( iii ) in a case where the consideration for the transfer consists of a thing or things and a`
  line `sum of money, the aggregate of the price that such thing or things would ordinarily fetch on`
  line `sale in the open market on the date on which the agreement for transfer is made, and such`
  line sum,
  line `and where the whole or any part of the consideration for such transfer is payable on any date or`
  line `dates falling after the date of such agreement for transfer, the value of the consideration payable`
  line `after such date shall be deemed to be the discounted value of such consideration, as on the date of`
  line `such agreement for transfer, determined by adopting such rate of interest as may be prescribed in`
  line `this behalf;`
  line `( c ) “appropriate authority” means an authority constituted under section 269UB to perform the`
  line `functions of an appropriate authority under this Chapter;`
  line `( d ) “immovable property” means—`
  line `( i ) any land or any building or part of a building, and includes, where any land or any`
  line `building or part of a building is to be transferred together with any machinery, plant, furniture,`
  line `fittings or other things, such machinery, plant, furniture, fittings or other things also.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- clause, “land, building, part of a building, machinery,`
  line `plant, furniture, fittings and other things” include an y rights therein;`
  line `( ii ) any rights in or with respect to any land or any building or a part of a building (whether or`
  line `not including any machinery, plant, furniture, fittings or other things therein) which has been`
  line `constructed or which is to be constructed, accruing or arising from any transaction (whether by`
  line `way of becoming a member of, or acquiring shares in, a co-operative society, company or other`
  line `association of persons or by way of any agreement or any arrangement of whatever nature), not`
  line `being a transaction by way of sale, exchange or lease of such land, building or part of a building;`
  line `( e ) “person interested”, in relation to any immovable property, includes all persons claiming, or`
  line `entitled to claim, an interest in the consideration payable on account of the vesting of that property in`
  line `the Central Government under this Chapter;`
  line `( f ) “transfer”,—`
  line `( i ) in relation to any immovable property referred to in sub-clause ( i ) of clause ( d ), means`
  line `transfer of such property by way of sale or exchange or lease for a term of not less than twelve`
  line `years, and includes allowing the possession of such property to be taken or retained in part`
  line `performance of a contract of the nature referred to in section 53A of the Transfer of Property Act,`
  line `1882 (4 of 1882).`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-clause, a lease which provides for the extension of the`
  line `term thereof by a further term or terms shall be deemed to be a lease for a term of not less than twelve`
  line `years, if the aggregate of the term for which such lease is to be granted and the further term or terms for`
  line `which it can be so extended is not less than twelve years;`
  line `( ii ) in relation to any immovable property of the nature referred to in sub-clause ( ii ) of`
  line `clause ( d ), means the doing of anything (whether by way of admitting as a member of or by way`
  line `of transfer of shares in a co-operative society or company or other association of persons or by`
  line `way of any agreement or arrangement or in any other manner whatsoever) which has the effect of`
  line `transferring, or enabling the enjoyment of, such property.`
  line `269UB. Appropriate authority. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may, by order, publish in the Official`
  line `Gazette, —`
  line `( a ) constitute as many appropriate authorities, as it thinks fit, to perform the functions of an`
  line `appropriate authority under this Chapter; and`
obj_root_law_sections_764_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_765:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-765
  sectionNo (765)
  orderNo 765
  title `Page 765`
  content obj_root_law_sections_765_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_765_footnotes
  sourcePage 765
obj_root_law_sections_765_content:
  string
  line 765
  line `( b ) define the local limits within which the appropriate authorities shall perform their functions`
  line `under this Chapter.`
  line `( 2 ) An appropriate authority shall consist of three persons, two of whom shall be members of the`
  line `Indian Income-tax Service, Group A, holding the post of Commissioner of Income-tax or any equivalent`
  line `or higher post, and one shall be a member of the Central Engineering Service, Group A, holding the post`
  line `of Chief Engineer or any equivalent or higher post.`
  line `( 3 ) In respect of any function to be performed by an appropriate authority under any provision of this`
  line `Chapter in relation to any immovable property referred to in section 269UC, the appropriate authority`
  line `referred to therein shall, —`
  line `( a ) in a case where such property is situate within the local limits of the jurisdiction of only one`
  line `appropriate authority, be such appropriate authority;`
  line `( b ) in a case where such property is situate within the local limits of the jurisdiction of two or`
  line `more appropriate authorities, be the appropriate authority empowered to perform such functions in`
  line `relation to such property in accordance with the rules made in this behalf by the Board under`
  line `section 295.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, immovable property being rights of the nature`
  line `referred to in sub-clause ( ii ) of clause ( d ) of section 269UA in, or with respect to, any land or any`
  line `building or part of a building which has been constructed or which is to be constructed shall be deemed to`
  line `be situate at the place where the land is situate or, as the case may be, where the building has been`
  line `constructed or is to be constructed.`
  line `269UC.Restrictions on transfer of immovable property. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in the Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882), or in any other law for the time being in force, 1 [no`
  line `transfer of any immovable property in such area and of such value exceeding five lakh rupees, as may be`
  line `prescribed], shall be effected except after an agreement for transfer is entered into between the person`
  line `who intends transferring the immovable property (hereinafter referred to as the transferor) and the person`
  line `to whom it is proposed to be transferred (hereinafter referred to as the transferee) in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) at least 2 [four months] before the intended date of transfer.`
  line `( 2 ) The agreement referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be reduced to writing in the form of a statement`
  line `by each of the parties to such transfer or by any of the parties to such transfer acting on behalf of himself`
  line `and on behalf of the other parties.`
  line `( 3 ) Every statement referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) shall, —`
  line `( i ) be in the prescribed form;`
  line `( ii ) set forth such particulars as may be prescribed; and`
  line `( iii ) be verified in the prescribed manner,`
  line `and shall be furnished to the appropriate authority in such manner and within such time as may be`
  line `prescribed, by each of the parties to such transaction or by any of the parties to such transaction acting on`
  line `behalf of himself and on behalf of the other parties.`
  line `3 [( 4 ) Where it is found that the statement referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) is defective, the appropriate`
  line `authority may intimate the defect to the parties concerned and give them an opportunity to rectify the`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 46, for “ no trans fer of any immovable property of such value exceeding five lakh rupees as`
  line `may be prescribed” (w.e.f. 1 -7-1995).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 38 of 1993, s. 33, for “three months” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1993).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 46 (w.e.f. 1-7-1995).`
obj_root_law_sections_765_footnotes:
