  line
obj_root_law_sections_766:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-766
  sectionNo (766)
  orderNo 766
  title `Page 766`
  content obj_root_law_sections_766_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_766_footnotes
  sourcePage 766
obj_root_law_sections_766_content:
  string
  line 766
  line `defect within a period of fifteen days from the date of such intimation or within such further period`
  line `which, on an application made in this behalf, the appropriate authority may, in its discretion, allow and if`
  line `the defect is not rectified within the said period of fifteen days, or as the case may be, the further period`
  line `so allowed, then, notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Chapter, the statement`
  line `shall be deemed never to have been furnished.]`
  line `269UD. Order by appropriate authority for purchase by Central Government of immovable`
  line `property. — ( 1 ) 1 [Subject to the provisions of sub-sections ( 1A ) and ( 1B ), the appropriate authority], after`
  line `the receipt of the statement under sub-section ( 3 ) of section 269UC in respect of any immovable property,`
  line `may, notwithstanding anything contained in any other law or any instrument or any agreement for the`
  line `time being in force, 2 *** make an order for the purchase by the Central Government of such immovable`
  line `property at an amount equal to the amount of apparent consideration:`
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made in respect of any immovable property after the expiration`
  line `of a period of two months from the end of the month in which the statement referred to in section`
  line `269UC in respect of such property is received by the appropriate authority:`
  line `3 [Provided further that where the statement referred to in section 269UC in respect of any immovable`
  line `property is received by the appropriate authority on or after the 1st day of June, 1993, the provisions of`
  line `the first proviso shall have effect as if for the words “ two months ”, the words “three months” had been`
  line `substituted:]`
  line `4 [Provided also that the period of limitation referred to in the second proviso shall be reckoned, where`
  line `any defect as referred to in sub-section ( 4 ) of section 269UC has been intimated, with reference to the`
  line `date of receipt of the rectified statement by the appropriate authority:]`
  line `5 [Provided also] that in a case where the statement referred to in section 269UC in respect of the`
  line `immovable property concerned is given to an appropriate authority, other than the appropriate authority`
  line `having jurisdiction in accordance with the provisions of section 269UB to make the order referred to in`
  line `this sub-section in relation to the immovable property concerned, the period of limitation referred to`
  line `in 6 [the first and second provisos] shall be reckoned with reference to the date of receipt of the statement`
  line `by the appropriate authority having jurisdiction to make the order under this sub-section:`
  line `7 [Provided also that the period of limitation referred to in the second proviso shall be reckoned, where`
  line `any stay has been granted by any court against the passing of an order for the purchase of the immovable`
  line `property under this Chapter, with reference to the date of vacation of the said stay.]`
  line `8 [( 1A ) Before making an order under sub-section ( 1 ), the appropriate authority shall give a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard to the transferor, the person in occupation of the immovable property if the`
  line `transferor is not in occupation of the property, the transferee and to every other person whom the`
  line `appropriate authority knows to be interested in the property.`
  line `( 1B ) Every order made by the appropriate authority under sub-section ( 1 ) shall specify the grounds on`
  line `which it is made.]`
  line `( 2 ) The appropriate authority shall cause a copy of its order under sub-section ( 1 ) in respect of any`
  line `immovable property to be served on the transferor, the person in occupation of the immovable property if`
  line `the transferor is not in occupation thereof, the transferee, and on every other person whom the appropriate`
  line `authority knows to be interested in the property.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1993, s. 34, for “The appropriate authority” (w.e.f. 17 -11-1992).`
  line `2. The words “and for reasons to be recorded in writing” omitted by s. 34, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-11-1992).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 34, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-1993).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-7-1995).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 38 of 1993, s. 34, for “Provided further” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1993).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 34, ibid., for “the preceding proviso” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1993).`
  line `7. Ins. by s. 34, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-1993).`
  line `8. Ins. by s. 34, ibid. (w.r.e.f. 17-11-1992).`
obj_root_law_sections_766_footnotes:
