obj_root_law_sections_767:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-767
  sectionNo (767)
  orderNo 767
  title `Page 767`
  content obj_root_law_sections_767_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_767_footnotes
  sourcePage 767
obj_root_law_sections_767_content:
  string
  line 767
  line `269UE. Vesting of property in Central Government. — ( 1 ) Where an order under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 269UD is made by the appropriate authority in respect of an immovable property referred to in`
  line `sub-clause ( i ) of clause ( d ) of section 269UA, such property shall, on the date of such order, vest in the`
  line `Central Government 1 [in terms of the agreement for transfer referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section`
  line `269UC]:`
  line `2 [Provided that where the appropriate authority, after giving an opportunity of being heard to the`
  line `transferor, the transferee or other persons interested in the said property, under sub-section ( 1A ) of section`
  line `269UD, is of the opinion that any encumbrance on the property or leasehold interest specified in the`
  line `aforesaid agreement for transfer is so specified with a view to defeat the provisions of this Chapter, it`
  line `may, by order, declare such encumbrance or leasehold interest to be void and thereupon the aforesaid`
  line `property shall vest in the Central Government free from such encumbrance or leasehold interest.]`
  line `( 2 ) The transferor or any other person who may be in possession of the immovable property in respect`
  line `of which an order under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 269UD is made, shall surrender or deliver possession`
  line `thereof to the appropriate authority or any other person duly authorised by the appropriate authority in`
  line `this behalf within fifteen days of the service of such order on him:`
  line `2 [Provided that the provisions of this sub-section and sub-sections ( 3 ) and ( 4 ) shall not apply where`
  line `the person in possession of the immovable property, in respect of which an order under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 269UD is made, is a bona fide holder of any encumbrance on such property or a bona`
  line `fide lessee of such property, if the said encumbrance or lease has not been declared void under the proviso`
  line `to sub-section ( 1 ) and such person is eligible to continue in possession of such property even after the`
  line `transfer in terms of the aforesaid agreement for transfer.]`
  line `( 3 ) If any person refuses or fails to comply with the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ), the appropriate`
  line `authority or other person duly authorised by it under that sub-section may take possession of the`
  line `immovable property and may, for that purpose, use such force as may be necessary.`
  line `( 4 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 2 ), the appropriate authority may, for the`
  line `purpose of taking possession of any property referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), requisition the services of any`
  line `police officer to assist him and it shall be the duty of such officer to comply with such requisition.`
  line `( 5 ) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that nothing in this section shall operate to`
  line `discharge the transferor or any other person (not being the Central Government) from liability in respect`
  line `of any encumbrances on the property and, notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, such liability may be enforced against the transferor or such other person.`
  line `( 6 ) Where an order under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 269UD is made in respect of an immovable`
  line `property, being rights of the nature referred to in sub-clause ( ii ) of clause ( d ) of section 269UA, such`
  line `order shall have the effect of —`
  line `( a ) vesting such right in the Central Government; and`
  line `( b ) placing the Central Government in the same position in relation to such rights as the person in`
  line `whom such a right would have continued to vest if such order had not been made.`
  line `( 7 ) Where any rights in respect of any immovable property, being rights in, or with respect to, any`
  line `land or any building or part of a building which has been constructed or which is to be constructed, have`
  line `been vested in the Central Government under sub-section ( 6 ), the provisions of sub-sections ( 1 ), ( 2 ), ( 3 )`
  line `and ( 4 ) shall, so far as may be, have effect as if the references to immovable property therein were`
  line `references to such land or building or part thereof, as the case may be.`
  line `1. Su bs. by Act 38 of 1993, s. 35, for “free from all encumbrances” (w.e.f. 17 -11-1992).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 35, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-11-1992).`
