  title `Page 768`
  content obj_root_law_sections_768_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_768_footnotes
  sourcePage 768
obj_root_law_sections_768_content:
  string
  line 768
  line `269UF. Consideration for purchase of immovable property by Central Government. — ( 1 )`
  line `Where an order for the purchase of any immovable property by the Central Government is made under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 269UD, the Central Government shall pay, by way of consideration for such`
  line `purchase, an amount equal to the amount of the apparent consideration.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), where, after the agreement for the transfer`
  line `of the immovable property referred to in that sub-section has been made but before the property vests in`
  line `the Central Government under section 269UE, the property has been damaged (otherwise than as a result`
  line `of normal wear and tear), the amount of the consideration payable under that sub-section shall be reduced`
  line `by such sum as the appropriate authority, for reasons to be recorded in writing, may by order determine.`
  line `269UG. Payment or deposit of consideration. — ( 1 ) The amount of consideration payable in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of section 269UF shall be tendered to the person or persons entitled`
  line `thereto, within a period of one month from the end of the month in which the immovable property`
  line `concerned becomes vested in the Central Government under sub-section ( 1 ), or, as the case may be, sub-`
  line `section ( 6 ), of section 269UE:`
  line `Provided that if any liability for any tax or any other sum remaining payable under this Act, the`
  line `Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957), the Gift-tax Act, 1958 (18 of 1958), the Estate Duty Act,`
  line `1953 (34 of 1953), or the Companies (Profits) Surtax Act, 1964 (7 of 1964), by any person entitled to the`
  line `consideration payable under section 269UF, the appropriate authority may, in lieu of the payment of the`
  line `amount of consideration, set off the amount of consideration or any part thereof against such liability or`
  line `sum, after giving an intimation in this behalf to the person entitled to the consideration.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), if any dispute arises as to the`
  line `apportionment of the amount of consideration amongst persons claiming to be entitled thereto, the Central`
  line `Government shall deposit with the appropriate authority the amount of consideration required to be`
  line `tendered under sub-section ( 1 ) within the period specified therein.`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), if the person entitled to the amount of`
  line `consideration does not consent to receive it, or if there is any dispute as to the title to receive the amount`
  line `of consideration, the Central Government shall deposit with the appropriate authority the amount of`
  line `consideration required to be tendered under sub-section ( 1 ) within the period specified therein:`
  line `Provided that nothing herein contained shall affect the liability of any person who may receive the`
  line `whole or any part of the amount of consideration for any immovable property vested in the Central`
  line `Government under this Chapter to pay the same to the person lawfully entitled thereto.`
  line `( 4 ) Where any amount of consideration has been deposited with the appropriate authority under this`
  line `section, the appropriate authority may, either of its own motion or on an application made by or on behalf`
  line `of any person interested or claiming to be interested in such amount, order the same to be invested in such`
  line `Government or other securities as it may think proper, and may direct the interest or other proceeds of any`
  line `such investment to be accumulated and paid in such manner as will, in its opinion, give the parties`
  line `interested therein the same benefits therefrom as they might have had from the immovable property in`
  line `respect whereof such amount has been deposited or as near thereto as may be.`
  line `269UH. Re-vesting of property in the transferor on failure of payment or deposit of`
  line `consideration. — ( 1 ) If the Central Government fails to tender under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 269UG or`
  line `deposit under sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-section ( 3 ) of the said section, the whole or any part of the amount of`
  line `consideration required to be tendered or deposited thereunder within the period specified therein in`
  line `respect of any immovable property which has vested in the Central Government under sub-section ( 1 ) or,`
obj_root_law_sections_768_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_769:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-769
  sectionNo (769)
  orderNo 769
  title `Page 769`
  content obj_root_law_sections_769_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_769_footnotes
  sourcePage 769
obj_root_law_sections_769_content:
  string
  line 769
  line `as the case may be, sub-section ( 6 ) of section 269UE, the order to purchase the immovable property by`
  line `the Central Government made under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 269UD shall stand abrogated and the`
  line `immovable property shall stand re-vested in the transferor after the expiry of the aforesaid period:`
  line `Provided that where any dispute referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-section ( 3 ) of section 269UG is`
  line `pending in any court for decision, the time taken by the court to pass a final order under the said`
  line `sub-sections shall be excluded in computing the said period.`
  line `( 2 ) Where an order made under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 269UD is abrogated and the immovable`
  line `property re-vested in the transferor under sub-section ( 1 ), the appropriate authority shall make, as soon as`
  line `may be, a declaration in writing to this effect and shall —`
  line `( a ) deliver a copy of the declaration to the persons mentioned in sub-section ( 2 ) of section`
  line `269UD; and`
  line `( b ) deliver or cause to be delivered possession of the immovable property back to the transferor,`
  line `or, as the case may be, to such other person as was in possession of the property at the time of its`
  line `vesting in the Central Government under section 269UE.`
  line `269UI. Powers of the appropriate authority. — The appropriate authority shall have, for the`
  line `purposes of this Chapter, all the powers that a 1 [ 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner]`
  line `or 3 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] of Income-tax has for the purposes of this Act under`
  line `section 131.`
  line `269UJ. Rectification of mistakes. — With a view to rectifying any mistake apparent from the record,`
  line `the appropriate authority may amend any order made by it under this Chapter, either on its own motion or`
  line `on the mistake being brought to its notice by any person affected by the order:`
  line `Provided that if any such amendment is likely to affect any person prejudicially, it shall not be made`
  line `without giving to such person a reasonable opportunity of being heard:`
  line `Provided further that no amendment shall be made under this section after the expiry of six months`
  line `from the end of the month in which the order sought to be amended was made.`
  line `269UK. Restrictions on revocation or alteration of certain agreements for the transfer of`
  line `immovable property or on transfer of certain immovable property. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other law for the time being in force, no person shall revoke or alter an agreement for the`
  line `transfer of an immovable property or transfer such property in respect of which a statement has been`
  line `furnished under section 269UC unless, —`
  line `( a ) the appropriate authority has not made an order for the purchase of the immovable property`
  line `by the Central Government under section 269UD and the period specified for the making of such`
  line `order has expired; or`
  line `( b ) in a case where an order for the purchase of the immovable property by the Central`
  line `Government has been made under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 269UD, the order stands abrogated under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 269UH.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4 for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_769_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_770:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-770
  sectionNo (770)
  orderNo 770
  title `Page 770`
  content obj_root_law_sections_770_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_770_footnotes
  sourcePage 770
obj_root_law_sections_770_content:
  string
  line 770
  line `( 2 ) Any transfer of any immovable property made in contravention of the provisions of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) shall be void.`
  line `269UL. Restrictions on registration, etc., of documents in respect of transfer of immovable`
  line `property. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, no`
  line `registering officer appointed under the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), shall register any document`
  line `which purports to transfer immovable property exceeding the value prescribed under`
  line `section 269UC unless a certificate from the appropriate authority that it has no objection to the transfer of`
  line `such property for an amount equal to the apparent consideration therefor as stated in the agreement for`
  line `transfer of the immovable property in respect of which it has received a statement under sub-section ( 3 )`
  line `of section 269UC, is furnished along with such document.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, no person shall`
  line `do anything or omit to do anything which will have the effect of transfer of any immovable property`
  line `unless the appropriate authority certifies that it has no objection to the transfer of such property for an`
  line `amount equal to the apparent consideration therefor as stated in the agreement for transfer of the`
  line `immovable property in respect of which it has received a statement under sub-section ( 3 ) of`
  line `section 269UC.`
  line `( 3 ) In a case where the appropriate authority does not make an order under sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 269UD for the purchase by the Central Government of an immovable property, or where the order`
  line `made under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 269UD stands abrogated under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 269UH,`
  line `the appropriate authority shall issue a certificate of no objection referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) or, as the`
  line `case may be, sub-section ( 2 ) and deliver copies thereof to the transferor and the transferee.`
  line `269UM. Immunity to transferor against claims of transferee for transfer. — Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in any other law or in any instrument or any agreement for the time being in force,`
  line `when an order for the purchase of any immovable property by the Central Government is made under this`
  line `Chapter, no claim by the transferee shall lie against the transferor by reason of such transfer being not in`
  line `accordance with the agreement for the transfer of the immovable property entered into between the`
  line `transferor and transferee:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall apply if the order for the purchase of the`
  line `immovable property by the Central Government is abrogated under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 269UH.`
  line `269UN. Order of appropriate authority to be final and conclusive. — Save as otherwise provided`
  line `in this Chapter, any order made under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 269UD or any order made under`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 269UF shall be final and conclusive and shall not be called in question in any`
  line `proceeding under this Act or under any other law for the time being in force.`
  line `269UO. Chapter not to apply to certain transfers. — The provisions of this Chapter shall not apply`
  line `to or in relation to any immovable property where the agreement for transfer of such property is made by`
  line `a person to his relative on account of natural love and affection, if a recital to that effect is made in the`
  line `agreement for transfer.`
  line `1 [ 269UP. Chapter not to apply where transfer of immovable property effected after certain`
  line `date. — The provisions of this Chapter shall not apply to, or in relation to, the transfer of any immovable`
  line `property effected on or after the 1st day of July, 2002.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 100 (w.e.f. 1-7-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_770_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_771:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-771
  sectionNo (771)
  orderNo 771
  title `Page 771`
  content obj_root_law_sections_771_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_771_footnotes
  sourcePage 771
obj_root_law_sections_771_content:
  string
  line 771
  line `CHAPTER XXI`
  line `P ENALTIES I MPOSABLE`
  line `270. [Failure to furnish information regarding securities, etc. ]. — Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws`
  line `( Amendment ) Act 1987 (4 of 1988), s. 105 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `1 [ 270A. Penalty for under-reporting and misreporting of income. — ( 1 ) The Assessing Officer or`
  line `the Commissioner (Appeals) or the Principal Commissioner or Commissioner may, during the course of`
  line `any proceedings under this Act, direct that any person who has under-reported his income shall be liable`
  line `to pay a penalty in addition to tax, if any, on the under-reported income.`
  line `( 2 ) A person shall be considered to have under-reported his income, if —`
  line `( a ) the income assessed is greater than the income determined in the return processed under`
  line `clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143;`
  line `( b ) the income assessed is greater than the maximum amount not chargeable to tax, where no`
  line `return of income has been furnished;`
  line `( c ) the income reassessed is greater than the income assessed or reassessed immediately before`
  line `such reassessment;`
  line `( d ) the amount of deemed total income assessed or reassessed as per the provisions of`
  line `section 115JB or section 115JC, as the case may be, is greater than the deemed total income`
  line `determined in the return processed under clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143;`
  line `( e ) the amount of deemed total income assessed as per the provisions of section 115JB or`
  line `section 115JC is greater than the maximum amount not chargeable to tax, where no return of income`
  line `has been filed;`
  line `( f ) the amount of deemed total income reassessed as per the provisions of`
  line `section 115JB or section 115JC, as the case may be, is greater than the deemed total income assessed`
  line `or reassessed immediately before such reassessment;`
  line `( g ) the income assessed or reassessed has the effect of reducing the loss or converting such loss`
  line `into income.`
  line `( 3 ) The amount of under-reported income shall be, —`
  line `( i ) in a case where income has been assessed for the first time, —`
  line `( a ) if return has been furnished, the difference between the amount of income assessed and`
  line `the amount of income determined under clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143;`
  line `( b ) in a case where no return has been furnished, —`
  line `( A ) the amount of income assessed, in the case of a company, firm or local authority; and`
  line `( B ) the difference between the amount of income assessed and the maximum amount not`
  line `chargeable to tax, in a case not covered in item (A);`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 98 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
