obj_root_law_sections_772_content:
  string
  line 772
  line `( ii ) in any other case, the difference between the amount of income reassessed or recomputed and`
  line `the amount of income assessed, reassessed or recomputed in a preceding order:`
  line `Provided that where under-reported income arises out of determination of deemed total income in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of section 115JB or section 115JC, the amount of total under-reported`
  line `income shall be determined in accordance with the following formula —`
  line `(A — B) + (C — D)`
  line where,
  line `A = the total income assessed as per the provisions other than the provisions contained`
  line `in section 115JB or section 115JC (herein called general provisions);`
  line `B = the total income that would have been chargeable had the total income assessed as per`
  line `the general provisions been reduced by the amount of under-reported income;`
  line `C = the total income assessed as per the provisions contained in section 115JB or section`
  line 115JC;
  line `D = the total income that would have been chargeable had the total income assessed as per`
  line `the provisions contained in section 115JB or section 115JC been reduced by the amount of under-`
  line `reported income:`
  line `Provided further that where the amount of under-reported income on any issue is considered`
  line `both under the provisions contained in section 115JB or section 115JC and under general`
  line `provisions, such amount shall not be reduced from total income assessed while determining the`
  line `amount under item D.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “preceding order” means an order immediately preceding the ord er during the course of which`
  line `the penalty under sub-section ( 1 ) has been initiated;`
  line `( b ) in a case where an assessment or reassessment has the effect of reducing the loss declared in`
  line `the return or converting that loss into income, the amount of under-reported income shall be the`
  line `difference between the loss claimed and the income or loss, as the case may be, assessed or`
  line reassessed.
  line `( 4 ) Subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 6 ), where the source of any receipt, deposit or investment`
  line `in any assessment year is claimed to be an amount added to income or deducted while computing loss, as`
  line `the case may be, in the assessment of such person in any year prior to the assessment year in which such`
  line `receipt, deposit or investment appears (hereinafter referred to as “preceding year”) and no penalty was`
  line `levied for such preceding year, then, the under-reported income shall include such amount as is sufficient`
  line `to cover such receipt, deposit or investment.`
  line `( 5 ) The amount referred to in sub-section ( 4 ) shall be deemed to be amount of income under-reported`
  line `for the preceding year in the following order —`
  line `( a ) the preceding year immediately before the year in which the receipt, deposit or investment`
  line `appears, being the first preceding year; and`
  line `( b ) where the amount added or deducted in the first preceding year is not sufficient to cover the`
  line `receipt, deposit or investment, the year immediately preceding the first preceding year and so on.`
obj_root_law_sections_772_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_773:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-773
  sectionNo (773)
  orderNo 773
  title `Page 773`
  content obj_root_law_sections_773_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_773_footnotes
  sourcePage 773
obj_root_law_sections_773_content:
  string
  line 773
  line `( 6 ) The under-reported income, for the purposes of this section, shall not include the following,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( a ) the amount of income in respect of which the assessee offers an explanation and the Assessing`
  line `Officer or the Commissioner (Appeals) or the Commissioner or the Principal Commissioner, as the`
  line `case may be, is satisfied that the explanation is bona fide and the assessee has disclosed all the`
  line `material facts to substantiate the explanation offered;`
  line `( b ) the amount of under-reported income determined on the basis of an estimate, if the accounts`
  line `are correct and complete to the satisfaction of the Assessing Officer or the Commissioner (Appeals)`
  line `or the Commissioner or the Principal Commissioner, as the case may be, but the method employed is`
  line `such that the income cannot properly be deduced therefrom;`
  line `( c ) the amount of under-reported income determined on the basis of an estimate, if the assessee`
  line `has, on his own, estimated a lower amount of addition or disallowance on the same issue, has`
  line `included such amount in the computation of his income and has disclosed all the facts material to the`
  line `addition or disallowance;`
  line `( d ) the amount of under-reported income represented by any addition made in conformity with`
  line `the arm’s length price determined by the Transfer Pricing Officer, where the assessee had maintained`
  line `information and documents as prescribed under section 92D, declared the international transaction`
  line `under Chapter X, and, disclosed all the material facts relating to the transaction; and`
  line `( e ) the amount of undisclosed income referred to in section 271AAB.`
  line `( 7 ) The penalty referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be a sum equal to fifty per cent of the amount of`
  line `tax payable on under-reported income.`
  line `( 8 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 6 ) or sub-section ( 7 ), where under-reported`
  line `income is in consequence of any misreporting thereof by any person, the penalty referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) shall be equal to two hundred per cent of the amount of tax payable on under-reported`
  line income.
  line `( 9 ) The cases of misreporting of income referred to in sub-section ( 8 ) shall be the following,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( a ) misrepresentation or suppression of facts;`
  line `( b ) failure to record investments in the books of account;`
  line `( c ) claim of expenditure not substantiated by any evidence;`
  line `( d ) recording of any false entry in the books of account;`
  line `( e ) failure to record any receipt in books of account having a bearing on total income; and`
  line `( f ) failure to report any international transaction or any transaction deemed to be an international`
  line `transaction or any specified domestic transaction, to which the provisions of Chapter X apply.`
  line `( 10 ) The tax payable in respect of the under-reported income shall be —`
  line `( a ) where no return of income has been furnished and the income has been assessed for the first`
  line `time, the amount of tax calculated on the under-reported income as increased by the maximum`
  line `amount not chargeable to tax as if it were the total income;`
obj_root_law_sections_773_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_774:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-774
  sectionNo (774)
