  title `Page 774`
  content obj_root_law_sections_774_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_774_footnotes
  sourcePage 774
obj_root_law_sections_774_content:
  string
  line 774
  line `( b ) where the total income determined under clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143 or`
  line `assessed, reassessed or recomputed in a preceding order is a loss, the amount of tax calculated on the`
  line `under-reported income as if it were the total income;`
  line `( c ) in any other case, determined in accordance with the formula —`
  line `(X-Y)`
  line where,
  line `X = the amount of tax calculated on the under-reported income as increased by the total`
  line `income determined under clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143 or total income assessed,`
  line `reassessed or recomputed in a preceding order as if it were the total income; and`
  line `Y = the amount of tax calculated on the total income determined under clause ( a ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 143 or total income assessed, reassessed or recomputed in a preceding`
  line order.
  line `( 11 ) No addition or disallowance of an amount shall form the basis for imposition of penalty, if such`
  line `addition or disallowance has formed the basis of imposition of penalty in the case of the person for the`
  line `same or any other assessment year.`
  line `( 12 ) The penalty referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be imposed, by an order in writing, by the`
  line `Assessing Officer, the Commissioner (Appeals), the Commissioner or the Principal Commissioner, as the`
  line `case may be.]`
  line `1 [ 270AA. Immunity from imposition of penalty, etc. — ( 1 ) An assessee may make an application to`
  line `the Assessing Officer to grant immunity from imposition of penalty under section 270A and initiation of`
  line `proceedings under section 276C or section 276CC, if he fulfils the following conditions, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the tax and interest payable as per the order of assessment or reassessment under`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ) of section 143 or section 147, as the case may be, has been paid within the period`
  line `specified in such notice of demand; and`
  line `( b ) no appeal against the order referred to in clause ( a ) has been filed.`
  line `( 2 ) An application referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be made within one month from the end of the`
  line `month in which the order referred to in clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ) has been received and shall be made`
  line `in such form and verified in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 3 ) The Assessing Officer shall, subject to fulfilment of the conditions specified in sub-section ( 1 ) and`
  line `after the expiry of the period of filing the appeal as specified in clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 249, grant immunity from imposition of penalty under section 270A and initiation of proceedings`
  line `under section 276C or section 276CC, where the proceedings for penalty under section 270A has not been`
  line `initiated under the circumstances referred to in sub-section ( 9 ) of the said section 270A.`
  line `( 4 ) The Assessing Officer shall, within a period of one month from the end of the month in which the`
  line `application under sub-section ( 1 ) is received, pass an order accepting or rejecting such application:`
  line `Provided that no order rejecting the application shall be passed unless the assessee has been given an`
  line `opportunity of being heard.`
  line `( 5 ) The order made under sub-section ( 4 ) shall be final.`
  line `( 6 ) No appeal under section 246A or an application for revision under section 264 shall be admissible`
  line `against the order of assessment or reassessment, referred to in clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ), in a case`
  line `where an order under sub-section ( 4 ) has been made accepting the application.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 99 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
