obj_root_law_sections_775_content:
  string
  line 775
  line `1 [ 271. Failure to furnish returns, comply with notices, concealment of income, etc. — ( 1 ) If the`
  line `2 [Assessing Officer] or the 3 *** 4 [Commissioner (Appeals)] 5 [or the 6 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner]] in the course of any proceedings under this Act, is satisfied that any person —`
  line `7 * * * * *]`
  line `( b ) has 8 *** failed to comply with a notice 9 [under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 115WD or under`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 115WE or under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142] or sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 143 10 [or fails to comply with a direction issued under sub-section ( 2A ) of section 142], or`
  line `( c ) has concealed the particulars of his income or 11 *** furnished inaccurate particulars of 12 [such`
  line `income, or]`
  line `13 [( d ) has concealed the particulars of the fringe benefits or furnished inaccurate particulars of`
  line `such fringe benefits,]`
  line `he may direct that such person shall pay by way of penalty, —`
  line `14 * * * * *`
  line `15 [( ii ) in the cases referred to in clause ( b ), 16 [in addition to tax, if any, payable] by him, 17 [a sum`
  line `of ten thousand rupees] for each such failure;]`
  line `18 [( iii ) in the cases referred to in 19 [clause ( c ) or clause ( d )], 16 [in addition to tax, if any, payable]`
  line `by him, a sum which shall not be less than, but which shall not exceed 20 [three times], the amount of`
  line `tax sought to be evaded by reason of the concealment of particulars of his 21 [income or fringe`
  line `benefits] or the furnishing of inaccurate particulars of such 21 [income or fringe benefits].`
  line `22 * * * * *]`
  line `Explanation 1. — Where in respect of any facts material to the computation of the total income of any`
  line `person under this Act, —`
  line `( A ) such person fails to offer an explanation or offers an explanation which is found by the`
  line `2 [Assessing Officer] or the 3 *** 4 [Commissioner (Appeals)] 5 [or the 6 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner]] to be false, or`
  line `1. Restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. The words “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or the” omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 101 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `7. Clause ( a ) omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `8. The words “without reasonable cause” omitted by Act 46 of 1986, s. 19 (w.e.f. 10 -9-1986).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 58, for “under sub -section ( 1 ) of section 142” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 61 (w.e.f 1-4-1976).`
  line `11. The word “deliberately” omitted by Act 5 of 1964, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-4-1964).`
  line `12. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 58, for “such income” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `13. Ins. by s. 58, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `14. Clause ( i ) omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `15. Subs. by s. 50, ibid., for clause ( ii ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `16. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 101, for “in addition to any tax payable” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2003).`
  line `17. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001. s. 86, for “a sum which shall not be less than one thousand rupees but which may extend to`
  line `twenty-fiv e thousand rupee” (w.e.f 1 -6-2001).`
  line `18. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 61, for clause ( iii ) and the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `19. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 58, for “clause (c)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `20. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 50, for “twice” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `21. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 58, for “income’ (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `22. The proviso omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
