obj_root_law_sections_776_content:
  string
  line 776
  line `( B ) such person offers an explanation which he is 1 [not able to substantiate and fails to prove that`
  line `such explanation is bona fide and that all the facts relating to the same and material to the`
  line `computation of his total income have been disclosed by him,]`
  line `then, the amount added or disallowed in computing the total income of such person as a result thereof`
  line `shall, for the purposes of clause ( c ) of this sub-section, be deemed to represent the income in respect of`
  line `which particulars have been concealed.`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `Explanation 2. — Where the source of any receipt, deposit, outgoing or investment in any assessment`
  line `year is claimed by any person to be an amount which had been added in computing the income or`
  line `deducted in computing the loss in the assessment of such person for any earlier assessment year or years`
  line `but in respect of which no penalty under clause ( iii ) of this sub-section had been levied, that part of the`
  line `amount so added or deducted in such earlier assessment year immediately preceding the year in which the`
  line `receipt, deposit, outgoing or investment appears (such earlier assessment year hereafter in`
  line `this Explanation referred to as the first preceding year) which is sufficient to cover the amount`
  line `represented by such receipt, deposit or outgoing or value of such investment (such amount or value`
  line `hereafter in this Explanation referred to as the utilised amount) shall be treated as the income of the`
  line `assessee, particulars of which had been concealed or inaccurate particulars of which had been furnished`
  line `for the first preceding year; and where the amount so added or deducted in the first preceding year is not`
  line `sufficient to cover the utilised amount, that part of the amount so added or deducted in the year`
  line `immediately preceding the first preceding year which is sufficient to cover such part of the utilised`
  line `amount as is not so covered shall be treated to be the income of the assessee, particulars of which had`
  line `been concealed or inaccurate particulars of which had been furnished for the year immediately preceding`
  line `the first preceding year and so on, until the entire utilised amount is covered by the amounts so added or`
  line `deducted in such earlier assessment years.`
  line `3 [ Explanation 3. — Where any person 4 *** fails, without reasonable cause, to furnish within the period`
  line `specified in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 153 a return of his income which he is required to furnish`
  line `under section 139 in respect of any assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 1989,`
  line `and until the expiry of the period aforesaid, no notice has been issued to him under clause ( i ) of sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ) of section 142 or section 148 and the Assessing Officer or the 5 *** Commissioner (Appeals) is`
  line `satisfied that in respect of such assessment year such person has taxable income, then, such person shall,`
  line `for the purposes of clause ( c ) of this sub-section, be deemed to have concealed the particulars of his`
  line `income in respect of such assessment year, notwithstanding that such person furnishes a return of his`
  line `income at any time after the expiry of the period aforesaid in pursuance of a notice under section 148.]`
  line `6 [ Explanation 4. — For the purposes of clause ( iii ) of this sub-section, —`
  line `( a ) the amount of tax sought to be evaded shall be determined in accordance with the following`
  line `formula —`
  line `( A - B ) + ( C - D )`
  line where,
  line `A = amount of tax on the total income assessed as per the provisions other than the provisions`
  line `contained in section 115Jb or section 115JC (herein called general provisions);`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 19, for “not able to substantiate,” (w.e.f. 10 -9-1986).`
  line `2. The proviso omitted by s. 19, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 50, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier Explanation 3 amended by Act 29 of 1977,`
  line `s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `4. The words “who has not previously been assessed under this Act,’ omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 101 (w.e.f. 1 -4-2003).`
  line `5. The words “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or the” omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 70, for Explanation 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
