obj_root_law_sections_779_content:
  string
  line 779
  line `1 [( 1A ) Where any penalty is imposable by virtue of Explanation 2 to sub-section ( 1 ), proceedings for`
  line `the imposition of such penalty may be initiated notwithstanding that any proceedings under this Act in the`
  line `course of which such penalty proceedings could have been initiated under sub-section ( 1 ) have been`
  line completed.]
  line `2 [( 1B ) Where any amount is added or disallowed in computing the total income or loss of an assessee`
  line `in any order of assessment or reassessment and the said order contains a direction for initiation of penalty`
  line `proceedings under clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 1 ), such an order of assessment or reassessment shall be`
  line `deemed to constitute satisfaction of the Assessing Officer for initiation of the penalty proceedings under`
  line `the said clause ( c ).]`
  line `( 2 ) When the person liable to penalty is a registered firm or an unregistered firm which has been`
  line `assessed under 3 [clause ( b ) of section 183,] then notwithstanding anything contained in the other`
  line `provisions of this Act, the penalty imposable under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be the same amount as would be`
  line `imposable on that firm if that firm were an unregistered firm.`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `( 4 ) If the 5 [Assessing Officer] or the 6 [*** Commissioner (Appeals)] in the course of any proceedings`
  line `under this Act, is satisfied that the profits of a registered firm have been distributed otherwise than in`
  line `accordance with the shares of the partners as shown in the instrument of partnership on the basis of which`
  line `the firm has been registered under this Act, and that any partner has thereby returned his income below its`
  line `real amount, he may direct that such partner shall, in addition to the tax, if any, payable by him, pay by`
  line `way of penalty a sum not exceeding one and a half times the amount of tax which has been avoided, or`
  line `would have been avoided if the income returned by such partner had been accepted as his correct income;`
  line `and no refund or other adjustment shall be claimable by any other partner by reason of such direction.`
  line `7 * * * * *`
  line `8 [( 5 ) The provisions of this section as they stood immediately before their amendment by the Direct`
  line `Tax Laws (Amendment) Act, 1989 (3 of 1989) shall apply to and in relation to any assessment for the`
  line `assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1988, or any earlier assessment year and references`
  line `in this section to the other provisions of this Act shall be construed as references to those provisions as for`
  line `the time being in force and applicable to the relevant assessment year.]`
  line `9 [( 6 ) Any reference in this section to the income shall be construed as a reference to the income or`
  line `fringe benefits, as the case may be, and the provisions of this section shall, as far as may be, apply in`
  line `relation to any assessment in respect of fringe benefits also.]`
  line `10 [ (7) The provisions of this section shall not apply to and in relation to any assessment for the`
  line `assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 2017.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 61 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 52 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Now Section 183 omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 65 (1-4-1993).`
  line `4. Sub-section ( 3 ) omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier it was amended by Act 41 of 1975,`
  line `s. 61 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. The words and brackets “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or, as the case may be, the” omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 65`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-10-1998). Earlier “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)” was substituted for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner”`
  line `by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4- 1988) and the words and brackets “or, as the case may be, the Commissioner (Appeals)”`
  line `were inserted by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `7. Sub-sections ( 4A ) and ( 4B ) omitted by Act 41 of 1975, s. 61 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975). Earlier the said sub-sections was`
  line `inserted by Act 1 of 1965, s. 3 (w.e.f. 12-3-1965) and later on sub-section ( 4A ) was substituted by Act 42 of 1970, s. 48`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1971).]`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 50 (w.e.f.1-4-1989).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 58 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 100 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
