obj_root_law_sections_780_content:
  string
  line 780
  line `1 [ 271A. Failure to keep, maintain or retain books of account, documents, etc. — Without prejudice`
  line `to the provisions of 2 [section 270A or] section 271, if any person 3 *** fails to keep and maintain any such`
  line `books of account and other documents as required by section 44AA or the rules made thereunder, in`
  line `respect of any previous year or to retain such books of account and other documents for the period`
  line `specified in the said rules, the 4 [Assessing Officer] or the 5 [*** Commissioner (Appeals)] may direct that`
  line `such person shall pay, by way of penalty, 6 [ a sum of twenty-five thousand rupees].]`
  line `7 [ 271AA. Penalty for failure to keep and maintain information and document, etc., in respect of`
  line `certain transactions. — 8 [( 1 )] Without prejudice to the provisions of 9 [section 270A or] section`
  line `271 or section 271BA, if any person in respect of an 10 [international transaction or specified domestic`
  line `transaction], —`
  line `( i ) fails to keep and maintain any such information and document as required by sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `or sub-section ( 2 ) of section 92D;`
  line `( ii ) fails to report such transaction which he is required to do so; or`
  line `( iii ) maintains or furnishes an incorrect information or document,`
  line `the Assessing Officer or Commissioner (Appeals) may direct that such person shall pay, by way of`
  line `penalty, a sum equal to two per cent. of the value of each 10 [international transaction or specified`
  line `domestic transaction] entered into by such person.]`
  line `9 [( 2 ) If any person fails to furnish the information and the document as required under`
  line `sub-section ( 4 ) of section 92D, the prescribed income-tax authority referred to in the said sub-section may`
  line `direct that such person shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum of five hundred thousand rupees.]`
  line `11 [ 271AAA. Penalty where search has been initiated. — ( 1 ) The Assessing Officer may,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in any other provisions of this Act, direct that, in a case where search`
  line `has been initiated under section 132 on or after the 1st day of June, 2007 12 [but before the 1st day of`
  line `July, 2012], the assessee shall pay by way of penalty, in addition to tax, if any, payable by him, a sum`
  line `computed at the rate of ten per cent. of the undisclosed income of the specified previous year.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 62 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 101 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `3. The words “, without reasonable cause,” omitted by Act 46 of 1986, s. 20 (w.e.f. 10 -9-1986).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. The word s and brackets “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or the” omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `which was substituted as “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)” for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” by Act 4 of 1988,`
  line `s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988) and the wor ds and brackets “or the Commissioner (Appeals)” were inserted after “Appellate`
  line `Assistant Commissioner” by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 1 -4-1977).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 87, for “a sum which shall not be less than two thousan d rupees but which may extend to one`
  line `hundred thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2001).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 98, for section 271AA (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `8. Section 271AA renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 28 of 2016, s. 102 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `9. Ins. by s. 102, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 99, for “international transaction” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `11. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 77 (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `12. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 100 (w.e.f. 1-4-2012).`
