obj_root_law_sections_782_content:
  string
  line 782
  line `1 [ 271AAB. Penalty where search has been initiated. — ( 1 ) The Assessing Officer may,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in any other provisions of this Act, direct that, in a case where search`
  line `has been initiated under section 132 on or after the 1st day of July, 2012 2 [but before the date on which`
  line `the Taxation Laws (Second Amendment) Bill, 2016 receives the assent of the President], the assessee`
  line `shall pay by way of penalty, in addition to tax, if any, payable by him, —`
  line `( a ) a sum computed at the rate of ten per cent of the undisclosed income of the specified previous`
  line `year, if such assessee —`
  line `( i ) in the course of the search, in a statement under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 132, admits the`
  line `undisclosed income and specifies the manner in which such income has been derived;`
  line `( ii ) substantiates the manner in which the undisclosed income was derived; and`
  line `( iii ) on or before the specified date —`
  line `( A ) pays the tax, together with interest, if any, in respect of the undisclosed income; and`
  line `( B ) furnishes the return of income for the specified previous year declaring such`
  line `undisclosed income therein;`
  line `( b ) a sum computed at the rate of twenty per cent of the undisclosed income of the specified`
  line `previous year, if such assessee —`
  line `( i ) in the course of the search, in a statement under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 132, does not`
  line `admit the undisclosed income; and`
  line `( ii ) on or before the specified date —`
  line `( A ) declares such income in the return of income furnished for the specified previous`
  line `year; and`
  line `( B ) pays the tax, together with interest, if any, in respect of the undisclosed income;`
  line `( c ) a sum 3 [computed at the rate of sixty per cent.] of the undisclosed income of the specified`
  line `previous year, if it is not covered by the provisions of clauses ( a ) and ( b ).`
  line `2 [ ( 1A ) The Assessing Officer may, notwithstanding anything contained in any other provisions of this`
  line `Act, direct that, in a case where search has been initiated under section 132 on or after the date on which`
  line `the Taxation Laws (Second Amendment) Bill, 2016 receives the assent of the President, the assessee shall`
  line `pay by way of penalty, in addition to tax, if any, payable by him, —`
  line `( a ) a sum computed at the rate of thirty per cent of the undisclosed income of the specified`
  line `previous year, if the assessee —`
  line `( i ) in the course of the search, in a statement under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 132, admits the`
  line `undisclosed income and specifies the manner in which such income has been derived;`
  line `( ii ) substantiates the manner in which the undisclosed income was derived; and`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 101 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 48 of 2016, s. 3 (w.e.f. 15-12-2016).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 103, for “ which shall not be less than thirty per cent. but which shall not exceed ninety per`
  line `cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
