  content obj_root_law_sections_784_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_784_footnotes
  sourcePage 784
obj_root_law_sections_784_content:
  string
  line 784
  line `1 [ 271AAC. Penalty in respect of certain income. — ( 1 ) The Assessing Officer may, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act other than the provisions of section 271AAB, direct that, in a case where`
  line `the income determined includes any income referred to in section 68, section 69, section 69A, section`
  line `69B, section 69C or section 69D for any previous year, the assessee shall pay by way of penalty, in`
  line `addition to tax payable under section 115BBE, a sum computed at the rate of ten per cent of the tax`
  line `payable under clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115BBE:`
  line `Provided that no penalty shall be levied in respect of income referred to in section 68, section 69,`
  line `section 69A, section 69B, section 69C or section 69D to the extent such income has been included by the`
  line `assessee in the return of income furnished under section 139 and the tax in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115BBE has been paid on or before the end of the relevant`
  line `previous year.`
  line `( 2 ) No penalty under the provisions of section 270A shall be imposed upon the assessee in respect of`
  line `the income referred to in sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 3 ) The provisions of sections 274 and 275 shall, as far as may be, apply in relation to the penalty`
  line `referred to in this section.]`
  line `2 [ 271B. Failure to get accounts audited. — If any person fails 3 *** to get his accounts audited in`
  line `respect of any previous year or years relevant to an assessment year or 4 [furnish a report of such audit as`
  line `required under section 44AB], the 5 [Assessing Officer] may direct that such person shall pay, by way of`
  line `penalty, a sum equal to one-half per cent of the total sales, turnover or gross receipts, as the case may be,`
  line `in business, or of the gross receipts in profession, in such previous year or years or a sum of 6 [one`
  line `hundred fifty thousand rupees], whichever is less.]`
  line `7 [ 271BA. Penalty for failure to furnish report under section 92E. — If any person fails to furnish a`
  line `report from an accountant as required by section 92E, the Assessing Officer may direct that such person`
  line `shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum of one hundred thousand rupees.]`
  line `8 [ 271BB. Failure to subscribe to the eligible issue of capital. — Whoever fails to subscribe any`
  line `amount of subscription to the units issued under any scheme referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section`
  line `88A* to the eligible issue of capital under that sub-section within the period of six months specified`
  line `therein, may be directed by the 9 [Joint Commissioner] to pay, by way of penalty, a sum equal to twenty`
  line `per cent of such amount.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 48 of 2016, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `3. The words “, without reasonable cause,” omitted by Act 46 of 1986, s. 21 (w.e.f. 10 -9-1986).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 48, for “obtain a report of such audit as required under section 44AB or furnish the said repo rt`
  line `along with the return of his income filed under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139, or along with the return of income`
  line `furnished in response to a notice under clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142” (w.e.f. 1 -7-1995). Earlier certain`
  line `words were inserted by Act 26 of 1988, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 19 88, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 50, for “one hundred thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2011).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 89 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 43 (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `* Section 88A omitted by Act 33 of 1996, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-4-1994).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 3, for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
