  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_786_footnotes
  sourcePage 786
obj_root_law_sections_786_content:
  string
  line 786
  line `1 [ 271F. Penalty for failure to furnish return of income. — If a person who is required to furnish a`
  line `return of his income, as required under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139 or by the provisos to that`
  line `sub-section, fails to furnish such return before the end of the relevant assessment year, the Assessing`
  line `Officer may direct that such person shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum of five thousand rupees.]`
  line `2 [Provided that nothing contained in this section shall apply to and in relation to the return of income`
  line `required to be furnished for any assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 2018.]`
  line `3 [ 271FA. Penalty for failure to furnish 4 [ statement of financial transaction or reportable`
  line `account]. — If a person who is required to furnish 5 [a statement of financial transaction or reportable`
  line `account] under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 285BA, fails to furnish such 6 [statement] within the time`
  line `prescribed under sub-section ( 2 ) thereof, the income-tax authority prescribed under said sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `may direct that such person shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum of 7 [five hundred rupees] for every day`
  line `during which such failure continues:`
  line `Provided that where such person fails to furnish the 6 [statement] within the period specified in the`
  line `notice issued under sub-section ( 5 ) of section 285BA, he shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum of 8 [one`
  line `thousand rupees] for every day during which the failure continues, beginning from the day immediately`
  line `following the day on which the time specified in such notice for furnishing the 6 [statement] expires.]`
  line `9 [ 271FAA. Penalty for furnishing inaccurate statement of financial transaction or reportable`
  line `account. — If a person referred to in clause ( k ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 285BA, who is required to`
  line `furnish a statement under that section, provides inaccurate information in the statement, and where —`
  line `( a ) the inaccuracy is due to a failure to comply with the due diligence requirement prescribed`
  line `under sub-section ( 7 ) of section 285BA or is deliberate on the part of that person; or`
  line `( b ) the person knows of the inaccuracy at the time of furnishing the statement of financial`
  line `transaction or reportable account, but does not inform the prescribed income-tax authority or such`
  line `other authority or agency; or`
  line `( c ) the person discovers the inaccuracy after the statement of financial transaction or reportable`
  line `account is furnished and fails to inform and furnish correct information within the time specified`
  line `under sub-section ( 6 ) of section 285BA,`
  line `then, the prescribed income-tax authority may direct that such person shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum`
  line `of fifty thousand rupees.]`
  line `10 [ 271FAB. Penalty for failure to furnish statement or information or document by an eligible`
  line `investment fund. — If any eligible investment fund which is required to furnish a statement or any`
  line `information or document, as required under sub-section ( 5 ) of section 9A fails to furnish such statement`
  line `or information or document within the time prescribed under that sub-section, the income-tax authority`
  line `prescribed under the said sub-section may direct that such fund shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum of five`
  line `hundred thousand rupees.]`
  line `11 [ 271FB. Penalty for failure to furnish return of fringe benefits. — If an employer, who is required`
  line `to furnish a return of fringe benefits, as required under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115WD, fails to furnish`
  line `such return within the time prescribed under that sub-section, the Assessing Officer may direct that such`
  line `employer shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum of one hundred rupees for every day during which the`
  line `failure continues.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 102, for section 271F (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 86 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 58, for section 271FA (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 70, for “annual information return” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2015).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 70, ibid., for “an annual information return” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2015).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 70, ibid., for “return” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2015).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 53, for “one hundred rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2018).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 53, ibid., for “five hundred rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2018).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 71 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 73 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `11. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 59 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_786_footnotes:
