obj_root_law_sections_787:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-787
  sectionNo (787)
  orderNo 787
  title `Page 787`
  content obj_root_law_sections_787_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_787_footnotes
  sourcePage 787
obj_root_law_sections_787_content:
  string
  line 787
  line `1 [ 271G. Penalty for failure to furnish information or document under section 92D. — If any`
  line `person who has entered into an 2 [international transaction or specified domestic transaction] fails to`
  line `furnish any such information or document as required by sub-section ( 3 ) of section 92D, the Assessing`
  line `Officer 3 [or the Transfer Pricing Officer as referred to in section 92CA] or the Commissioner (Appeals)`
  line `may direct that such person shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum equal to two per cent of the value of the`
  line `2 [international transaction or specified domestic transaction for each such failure.]`
  line `4 [ 271GA. Penalty for failure to furnish information or document under section 285A. — If any`
  line `Indian concern, which is required to furnish any information or document under section 285A, fails to do`
  line `so, the income-tax authority, as may be prescribed under the said section, may direct that such Indian`
  line `concern shall pay, by way of penalty, —`
  line `( i ) a sum equal to two per cent of the value of the transaction in respect of which such failure has`
  line `taken place, if such transaction had the effect of directly or indirectly transferring the right of`
  line `management or control in relation to the Indian concern;`
  line `( ii ) a sum of five hundred thousand rupees in any other case.]`
  line `5 [ 271GB. Penalty for failure to furnish report or for furnishing inaccurate report under`
  line `section 286. — ( 1 ) If any reporting entity referred to in section 286, which is required to furnish the report`
  line `referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) of the said section, in respect of a reporting accounting year, fails to do so,`
  line `the authority prescribed under that section (herein referred to as prescribed authority) may direct that such`
  line `entity shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum of, —`
  line `( a ) five thousand rupees for every day for which the failure continues, if the period of failure does`
  line `not exceed one month; or`
  line `( b ) fifteen thousand rupees for every day for which the failure continues beyond the period of one`
  line month.
  line `( 2 ) Where any reporting entity referred to in section 286 fails to produce the information and`
  line `documents within the period allowed under sub-section ( 6 ) of the said section, the prescribed authority`
  line `may direct that such entity shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum of five thousand rupees for every day`
  line `during which the failure continues, beginning from the day immediately following the day on which the`
  line `period for furnishing the information and document expires.`
  line `( 3 ) If the failure referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) continues after an order has been`
  line `served on the entity, directing it to pay the penalty under sub-section ( 1 ) or, as the case may be, under`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ), then, notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ), the`
  line `prescribed authority may direct that such entity shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum of fifty thousand`
  line `rupees for every day for which such failure continues beginning from the date of service of such order.`
  line `( 4 ) Where a reporting entity referred to in section 286 provides inaccurate information in the report`
  line `furnished in accordance with sub-section ( 2 ) of the said section and where —`
  line `( a ) the entity has knowledge of the inaccuracy at the time of furnishing the report but fails to`
  line `inform the prescribed authority; or`
  line `( b ) the entity discovers the inaccuracy after the report is furnished and fails to inform the`
  line `prescribed authority and furnish correct report within a period of fifteen days of such discovery; or`
  line `( c ) the entity furnishes inaccurate information or document in response to the notice issued under`
  line `sub-section ( 6 ) of section 286,`
  line `then, the prescribed authority may direct that such person shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum of five lakh`
  line rupees.]
  line `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 91 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 102, for “international transaction” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2013).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 72 (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 74 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 104 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
