  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_788_footnotes
  sourcePage 788
obj_root_law_sections_788_content:
  string
  line 788
  line `1 [ 271H. Penalty for failure to furnish statements, etc. — ( 1 ) Without prejudice to the provisions of`
  line `the Act, the 2 [Assessing Officer may direct that a person shall pay by way of] penalty, if, he —`
  line `( a ) fails to deliver or cause to be delivered a statement within the time prescribed in sub-section`
  line `( 3 ) of section 200 or the proviso to sub-section ( 3 ) of section 206C; or`
  line `( b ) furnishes incorrect information in the statement which is required to be delivered or caused to`
  line `be delivered under sub-section ( 3 ) of section 200 or the proviso to sub-section ( 3 ) ofsection 206C.`
  line `( 2 ) The penalty referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be a sum which shall not be less than ten thousand`
  line `rupees but which may extend to one lakh rupees.`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, no penalty shall`
  line `be levied for the failure referred to in clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ), if the person proves that after paying`
  line `tax deducted or collected along with the fee and interest, if any, to the credit of the Central Government,`
  line `he had delivered or cause to be delivered the statement referred to in sub-section ( 3 ) of section 200 or the`
  line `proviso to sub-section ( 3 ) of section 206C before the expiry of a period of one year from the time`
  line `prescribed for delivering or causing to be delivered such statement.`
  line `( 4 ) The provisions of this section shall apply to a statement referred to in sub-section ( 3 ) of section`
  line `200 or the proviso to sub-section ( 3 ) of section 206C which is to be delivered or caused to be delivered`
  line `for tax deducted at source or tax collected at source, as the case may be, on or after the 1st day of July,`
  line 2012.
  line `3 [ 271-I. Penalty for failure to furnish information or furnishing inaccurate information`
  line `under section 195. — If a person, who is required to furnish information under sub-section ( 6 ) of section`
  line `195, fails to furnish such information, or furnishes inaccurate information, the Assessing Officer may`
  line `direct that such person shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum of one lakh rupees.]`
  line `4 [ 271J. Penalty for furnishing incorrect information in reports or certificates. — Without`
  line `prejudice to the provisions of this Act, where the Assessing Officer or the Commissioner (Appeals), in the`
  line `course of any proceedings under this Act, finds that an accountant or a merchant banker or a registered`
  line `valuer has furnished incorrect information in any report or certificate furnished under any provision of this`
  line `Act or the rules made thereunder, the Assessing Officer or the Commissioner (Appeals) may direct that such`
  line `accountant or merchant banker or registered valuer, as the case may be, shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum`
  line `of ten thousand rupees for each such report or certificate.`
  line `Explanation. –– For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “accountant” means an accountant referred to in the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 288;`
  line `( b ) “merchant banker” means Category I merchant banker registered with the Securities and`
  line `Exchange Board of India established under section 3 of the Securities and Exchange Board of India`
  line `Act, 1992.`
  line `( c ) “registered valuer” means a person defined in clause ( oaa ) of section 2 of the Wealth-tax Act,`
  line 1957.]
  line `[272. Failure to give notice of discontinuance.] — Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws ( Amendment )`
  line `Act, 1987, (4 of 1988), s. 109 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5 [ 272A. Penalty for failure to answer questions, sign statements, furnish information, returns or`
  line `statements, allow inspections, etc. — ( 1 ) If any person, —`
  line `( a ) being legally bound to state the truth of any matter touching the subject of his assessment,`
  line `refuses to answer any question put to him by an income-tax authority in the exercise of its powers`
  line `under this Act; or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 103 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 73, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 75 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 87 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 110 (w.e.f 1-4-1989). Prior to its inserted by Act 41 of 1975, s. 63 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
