obj_root_law_sections_789_content:
  string
  line 789
  line `( b ) refuses to sign any statement made by him in the course of any proceedings under this Act,`
  line `which an income-tax authority may legally require him to sign; or`
  line `( c ) to whom a summons is issued under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 131 either to attend to give`
  line `evidence or produce books of account or other documents at a certain place and time omits to attend`
  line `or produce books of account or documents at the 1 [place or time; or]`
  line `2 [( d )fails to comply with a notice under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142 or sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 143 or fails to comply with a direction issued under sub-section ( 2A ) of section 142,]`
  line `he shall pay, by way of penalty, 3 [a sum of ten thousand rupees] for each such default or failure.`
  line `( 2 ) If any person fails —`
  line `( a ) to comply with a notice issued under sub-section ( 6 ) of section 94; or`
  line `( b ) to give the notice of discontinuance of his business or profession as required by sub-section`
  line `( 3 ) of section 176; or`
  line `( c ) to furnish in due time any of the returns, statements or particulars mentioned in section`
  line `133 or section 206 4 *** 5 [or section 206C] or section 285B; or`
  line `( d ) to allow inspection of any register referred to in section 134 or of any entry in such register or`
  line `to allow copies of such register or of any entry therein to be taken; or`
  line `6 [( e ) to furnish the return of income which he is required to furnish under sub-section ( 4A ) or sub-`
  line `section ( 4C ) of section 139 or to furnish it within the time allowed and in the manner required under`
  line `those sub-sections; or]`
  line `( f ) to deliver or cause to be delivered in due time a copy of the declaration mentioned in section`
  line `197A; or`
  line `( g ) to furnish a certificate as required by section 203 5 [or section 206C]; or`
  line `( h ) to deduct and pay tax as required by sub-section ( 2 ) of section 226;`
  line `7 [( i ) to furnish a statement as required by sub-section ( 2C ) of section 192;]`
  line `8 [( j ) to deliver or cause to be delivered in due time a copy of the declaration referred to in sub-`
  line `section ( 1A ) of section 206C;]`
  line `9 [( k ) to deliver or cause to be delivered a copy of the statement within the time specified in sub-`
  line `section ( 3 ) of section 200 or the proviso to sub-section ( 3 ) of section 206C;]`
  line `10 [( l ) to deliver or cause to be delivered the 11 [statements] within the time specified in sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) of section 206A;]`
  line `12 [( m ) to deliver or cause to be delivered a statement within the time as may be prescribed under`
  line `sub-section ( 2A ) of section 200 or sub-section ( 3A ) of section 206C,]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 105, for “place or time, ” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 105, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 92, for “a sum which shall not be less than five hundred rupees but which niay extend to ten`
  line `thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2001).`
  line `4. The words, figures and letters “or section 206A or section 206B” omitted by Act 33 of 1996, s. 55 (w.e.f. 1 -10-1996).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 68 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 103, for clause ( e ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2003).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 92 (w.e.f. 1-4-2002).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 17, for clause ( j ) (w.e.f. 8-9-2003).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 56 (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 60 (w.e.f. 1-6-2005).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 75, for “quarterly return” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2009).`
  line `12. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 76 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
