  line 791
  line `( 2 ) No order under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be passed unless the person on whom the penalty is proposed`
  line `to be imposed is given an opportunity of being heard in the matter.]`
  line `1 [ 272B.Penalty for failure to comply with the provisions of section 139A. — ( 1 ) If a person fails to`
  line `comply with the provisions of section 139A, the Assessing Officer may direct that such person shall pay,`
  line `by way of penalty, a sum of ten thousand rupees.`
  line `( 2 ) If a person who is required to quote his permanent account number in any document referred to in`
  line `clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 5 ) of section 139A, or to intimate such number as required by sub-section ( 5A )`
  line `2 [or sub-section ( 5C )] of that section, quotes or intimates a number which is false, and which he either`
  line `knows or believes to be false or does not believe to be true, the Assessing Officer may direct that such`
  line `person shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum of ten thousand rupees.`
  line `( 3 ) No order under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) shall be passed unless the person, on whom the`
  line `penalty is proposed to be imposed, is given an opportunity of being heard in the matter.]`
  line `3 [ 272BB. Penalty for failure to comply with the provisions of section 203A. — ( 1 ) If a person fails`
  line `to comply with the provisions of section 203A, he shall, on an order passed by the 4 [Assessing Officer],`
  line `pay, by way of penalty, 5 [a sum of ten thousand rupees].`
  line `6 [( 1A ) If a person who is required to quote his “tax deduction account number” or, as the case may be,`
  line `“tax collection account number” or “tax deduction and collection account number” in the challans or`
  line `certificates or statements or other documents referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) of section 203A, quotes a`
  line `number which is false, and which he either knows or believes to be false or does not believe to be true,`
  line `the Assessing Officer may direct that such person shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum of ten thousand`
  line rupees.]
  line `( 2 ) No order under sub-section ( 1 ) 6 [or sub-section ( 1A )] shall be passed unless the person on whom`
  line `the penalty is proposed to be imposed is given an opportunity of being heard in the matter.]`
  line `7 [ 272BBB. Penalty for failure to comply with the provisions of section 206CA. — ( 1 ) If a person`
  line `8 [fails to comply before the 1st day of October, 2004] with the provisions of section 206CA, he shall, on`
  line `an order passed by the Assessing Officer, pay, by way of penalty, a sum of ten thousand rupees.`
  line `( 2 ) No order under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be passed unless the person on whom the penalty is proposed`
  line `to be imposed, is given an opportunity of being heard in the matter.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 104 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 57 (w.e.f 1-4-2005).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 68 (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 93, for “a sum which may extend to five thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2001).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 54 (w.e.f. 1-6-2006).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 105 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 58, for “fails to comply” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2004).`
