obj_root_law_sections_792_content:
  string
  line 792
  line `1 [ 273. False estimate of, or failure to pay, advance tax. — 2 [( 1 ) If the 3 [Assessing Officer], in the`
  line `course of any proceedings in connection with the regular assessment for any assessment year, is satisfied`
  line `that any assessee —`
  line `( a ) has furnished under clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 209A a statement of the advance`
  line `tax payable by him which he knew or had reason to believe to be untrue, or`
  line `( b ) has 4 *** failed to furnish a statement of the advance tax payable by him in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 209A,`
  line `he may direct that such person shall, in addition to the amount of tax, if any, payable by him, pay by way`
  line `of penalty a sum —`
  line `( i ) which, in the case referred to in clause ( a ), shall not be less than ten per cent but shall not`
  line `exceed one and a half times the amount by which the tax actually paid during the financial year`
  line `immediately preceding the assessment year under the provisions of Chapter XVIIC falls short of —`
  line `( 1 ) seventy-five per cent. of the assessed tax as defined in sub-section ( 5 ) of section 215, or`
  line `( 2 ) the amount which would have been payable by way of advance tax if the assessee had`
  line `furnished a correct and complete statement in accordance with the provisions of clause ( a ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 209A,`
  line `whichever is less;`
  line `( ii ) which, in the case referred to in clause ( b ), shall not be less than ten per cent. but shall not`
  line `exceed one and a half times of seventy-five per cent. of the assessed tax as defined in`
  line `sub-section ( 5 ) of section 215]:`
  line `5 [Provided that in the case of an assessee, being a company, the provisions of this sub-section shall`
  line `have effect as if for the words “seventy - five per cent.”, at both the places where they occur, the words`
  line `“eighty -three and one- third per cent.” had been substituted.]`
  line `6 [( 2 )] If the 3 [Assessing Officer], in the course of any proceedings in connection with the regular`
  line `assessment for the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1970, or any subsequent`
  line `assessment year, is satisfied that any assessee —`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 1969, s. 22, for section 273 (w.e.f. 1-4-1970).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 19 of 1978, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-6-1978).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. The words “, without reasonable cause,” omitted by Act 46 of 1986, s. 25 (w.e.f. 10 -9-1986).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-9-1980).`
  line `6. Section 273 renumbered as sub-section ( 2 ) thereof by Act 19 of 1978, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-6-1978).`
