  line 793
  line `1 [( a ) has furnished under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 5 )`
  line `of section 209A, or under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) of section 212, an estimate of the advance`
  line `tax payable by him which he knew or had reason to believe to be untrue, or]`
  line `2 [( aa ) has furnished 3 [under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 209A or] under sub-section ( 3A ) of`
  line `section 212 an estimate of the advance tax payable by him which he knew or had reason to believe to`
  line `be untrue, or]`
  line `( b ) has 4 *** failed to furnish an estimate of the advance tax payable by him in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of 5 [clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 209A], or`
  line `( c ) has 4 *** failed to furnish an estimate of the advance tax payable by him in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of 6 [sub-section ( 4 ) of section 209A or sub-section ( 3A ) of section 212],`
  line `he may direct that such person shall, in addition to the amount of tax, if any, payable by him, pay by way`
  line `of penalty a sum —`
  line `( i ) which, in the case referred to in clause ( a ), shall not be less than ten per cent. but shall not`
  line `exceed one and a half times the amount by which the tax actually paid during the financial year`
  line `immediately preceding the assessment year under the provisions of Chapter XVII-C falls short of —`
  line `( 1 ) seventy-five per cent of the assessed tax as defined in sub-section ( 5 ) of section 215, or`
  line `7 [( 2 ) where a statement under clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 209A was furnished by`
  line `the assessee or where a notice under section 210 was issued to the assessee, the amount payable`
  line `under such statement or, as the case may be, such notice,]`
  line `whichever is less;`
  line `2 [( ia ) which, in the case referred to in clause ( aa ), shall not be less than ten per cent. but shall not`
  line `exceed one and a half times the amount by which the tax actually paid during the financial year`
  line `immediately preceding the assessment year under the provisions of Chapter XVII-C falls short of`
  line `seventy-five per cent. of the assessed tax as defined in sub-section ( 5 ) of section 215;]`
  line `( ii ) which, in the case referred to in clause ( b ), shall not be less than ten per cent. but shall not`
  line `exceed one and a half times of seventy-five per cent of the assessed tax as defined in`
  line `sub-section ( 5 ) of section 215; and`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1978, s. 31, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 1-6-1978).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-9-1977).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 19 of 1978, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-6-1978).`
  line `4. The words “, without reasonable cause,” omitted by Act 46 of 1986, s. 25 (w.e.f. 10 -9-1986).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 19 of 1978, s. 31, for “sub -section ( 3 ) of section 212” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1978).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for “sub -section ( 3A ) of section 212” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1978).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for sub-clause ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-6-1978).`
