obj_root_law_sections_794_content:
  string
  line 794
  line `1 [( iii ) which, in the case referred to in clause ( c ), shall not be less than ten per cent. but shall not`
  line `exceed one and a half times the amount by which —`
  line `( a ) where the assessee has sent a statement under clause ( a ), or an estimate under clause ( b )`
  line `of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 209A, or an estimate in lieu of a statement under sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `that section, the tax payable in accordance with such statement or estimate; or`
  line `( b ) where the assessee was required to pay advance tax in accordance with the notice issued`
  line `to him under section 210, the tax payable under such notice,`
  line `falls short of seventy-five per cent. of the assessed tax as defined in sub-section ( 5 ) of`
  line `section 215:]]`
  line `2 [Provided that in the case of an assessee, being a company, the provisions of this sub-section shall`
  line `have effect as if for the words “seventy - five per cent.”, wherever they occur, the words “eighty -three and`
  line `one- third per cent.” had been substitute d.]`
  line `3 [ Explanation 4 [ 1 ]. — For the purposes of clause ( ia ), the amount paid by the assessee on or before the`
  line `date extended by the 5 [ 6 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 7 [Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner]] under the 8 [ 9 [first proviso] to sub-section ( 4 ) of section 209A or, as the`
  line `case may be, 9 [first proviso] to sub-section ( 3A ) of section 212] shall, where the date so extended falls`
  line `beyond the financial year immediately preceding the assessment year, also be regarded as tax actually`
  line `paid during that financial year.]`
  line `10 [ Explanation 2. — When the person liable to penalty is a registered firm or an unregistered firm`
  line `which has been assessed under clause ( b ) of section 183, then, notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `other provisions of this Act, the penalty imposable under this section shall be the same amount as would`
  line `be imposable on that firm if that firm were an unregistered firm.]`
  line `11 [( 3 ) The provisions of this section shall apply to and in relation to any assessment for the assessment`
  line `year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1988, or any earlier assessment year, and references in this`
  line `section to the other provisions of this Act shall be construed as references to those provisions as for the`
  line `time being in force and applicable to the relevant assessment year.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1978, s. 31, for clause ( iii ) (w.e.f. 1-6-1978).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-9-1980).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-9-1977).`
  line `4. The Explanation numbered as Explanation 1 by Act 67 of 1984, s. 49 (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 19 of 1978, s. 31, for “proviso to sub -section ( 3A ) of section 212” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1978).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 16 of 1981, s. 25, for “proviso” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1981).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 49 (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `11. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 112 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
