obj_root_law_sections_795_content:
  string
  line 795
  line `1 [ 273A. Power to reduce or waive penalty, etc., in certain cases. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act, the 2 [ 3 *** 4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] may, in his discretion,`
  line `whether on his own motion or otherwise, —`
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `( ii ) reduce or waive the amount of penalty imposed or imposable on a person under 6 [ section`
  line `270A or ] clause ( iii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 271; [or]`
  line `7 * * * * *`
  line `if he is satisfied that such person —`
  line `8 * * * * *`
  line `( b ) in the case referred to in clause ( ii ), has, prior to the detection by the 9 [Assessing Officer], of`
  line `the concealment of particulars of income or of the inaccuracy of particulars furnished in respect of`
  line `such income, voluntarily and in good faith, made full and true disclosure of such particulars,`
  line `10 * * * * *`
  line `and also has, 11 [in the case referred to in clause ( b )], co-operated in any enquiry relating to the assessment`
  line `of his income and has either paid or made satisfactory arrangements for the payment of any tax or interest`
  line `payable in consequence of an order passed under this Act in respect of the relevant assessment year.`
  line `Explanation. 12 *** — For the purposes of this sub-section, a person shall be deemed to have made full`
  line `and true disclosure of his income or of the particulars relating thereto in any case where the excess of`
  line `income assessed over the income returned is of such a nature as not to attract the provisions of`
  line `6 [ section 270A or ] clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 271.`
  line `12 * * * * *`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), —`
  line `13 * * * * *`
  line `( b ) if in a case falling under 6 [section 270A or] clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 271, the`
  line `amount of income in respect of which the penalty is imposed or imposable for the relevant assessment`
  line `year, or, where such disclosure relates to more than one assessment year, the aggregate amount of`
  line `such income for those years, exceeds a sum of five hundred thousand rupees,`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 64 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. The words “Chief Commissioner or” omitted by Act 38 of 1993, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1 -6-1993).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `5. Clause ( i ) omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 51 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 106 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `7. Clause ( iii ) omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 51 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `8. Clause ( a ) omitted by s. 51, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. (1 -4-1988).`
  line `10. Clause ( c ) omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 51 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `11. Subs. by s. 51, ibid., for “in all the cases refer red to in clauses ( a ), ( b ) and ( c )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `12. Explanation 2 omitted by Act 32 of 1985, s. 34 (w.e.f. 24-5- 1985).. Earlier “1” and Explanation 2 was ins. by`
  line `Act 67 of 1984, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line `13. Clause ( a ) omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 51 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier clause ( a ) was amended by Act 67 of 1984,`
  line `s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
