obj_root_law_sections_796_content:
  string
  line 796
  line `no order reducing or waiving the penalty under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be made by 1 [the 2 [Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner] except with the previous approval of the 3 [Principal Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 4 [Principal Director General or Director General], as the case`
  line `may be].`
  line `( 3 ) Where an order has been made under sub-section ( 1 ) in favour of any person, whether such order`
  line `relates to one or more assessment years, he shall not be entitled to any relief under this section in relation`
  line `to any other assessment year at any time after the making of such order:`
  line `5 [Provided that where an order has been made in favour of any person under sub-section ( 1 ) on or`
  line `before the 24th day of July, 1991, such person shall be entitled to further relief only once in relation to`
  line `other assessment year or years if he makes an application to the income-tax authority referred to in sub-`
  line `section ( 4 ) at any time before the 1st day of April, 1992.]`
  line `( 4 ) Without prejudice to the powers conferred on him by any other provision of this Act,`
  line `the 6 [ 7 *** 2 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] may, on an application made in this behalf by an`
  line `assessee, and after recording his reasons for so doing, reduce or waive the amount of any penalty payable`
  line `by the assessee under this Act or stay or compound any proceeding for the recovery of any such amount,`
  line `if he is satisfied that —`
  line `( i ) to do otherwise would cause genuine hardship to the assessee, having regard to the`
  line `circumstances of the case; and`
  line `( ii ) the assessee has co-operated in any inquiry relating to the assessment or any proceeding for`
  line `the recovery of any amount due from him:`
  line `8 [Provided that where the amount of any penalty payable under this Act or, where such`
  line `application relates to more than one penalty, the aggregate amount of such penalties exceeds one`
  line `hundred thousand rupees, no order reducing or waiving the amount or compounding any proceeding`
  line `for its recovery under this sub-section shall be made by 1 [the 2 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner] except with the previous approval of the 3 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner] or 4 [Principal Director General or Director General], as the case may be].]`
  line `9 [( 4A ) The order under sub-section ( 4 ), either accepting or rejecting the application in full or in part,`
  line `shall be passed within a period of twelve months from the end of the month in which the application`
  line `under the said sub-section is received by the Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner:`
  line `Provided that no order rejecting the application, either in full or in part, shall be passed unless the`
  line `assessee has been given an opportunity of being heard:`
  line `Provided further that where any application is pending as on the 1st day of June, 2016, the order shall`
  line `be passed on or before the 31st day of May, 2017.]`
  line `( 5 ) Every order made under this section shall be final and shall not be called into question by any`
  line `court or any other authority.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1993, s. 36, for “the Chief Commissioner or Commissioner except with the previous approval of the`
  line `Board” (w.e.f. 1 -6- 1993). Earlier the words “Chief Commissioner or Commissioner” were substituted by Act 4 of 1988, s.`
  line `2, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Chief Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Director General” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 69 (w.e.f. 27-9-1991).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. The words “Chief Commissioner or” omitted by Act 38 of 1993, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1 -6-1993).`
  line `8. The proviso added by Act 67 of 1984, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 106 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
