obj_root_law_sections_797_content:
  string
  line 797
  line `1 [( 6 ) The provisions of this section 2 [as they stood immediately before their amendment by the Direct`
  line `Tax Laws (Amendment) Act, 1989] shall apply to and in relation to any assessment for the assessment`
  line `year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1988, or any earlier assessment year, and references in this`
  line `section to the other provisions of this Act shall be construed as references to those provisions as for the`
  line `time being in force and applicable to the relevant assessment year.]`
  line `3 [( 7 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 6 ), the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ), sub-`
  line `section ( 2 ), or, as the case may be, sub-section ( 4 ) [as they stood immediately before their amendment by`
  line `the Direct Tax Laws (Amendment) Act, 1989 (3 of 1989)], shall apply in the case of reduction or waiver`
  line `of penalty or interest in relation to any assessment for the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 1988 or any earlier assessment year, with the modifications that the power under the said sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ) shall be exercisable only by the 4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] and instead of the`
  line `previous approval of the Board, the 4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] shall obtain the previous`
  line `approval of the 5 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 6 [Principal Director General`
  line `or Director General], as the case may be, while dealing with such case.]`
  line `7 [ 273AA. Power of 4 [ Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] to grant immunity from`
  line `penalty. — ( 1 ) A person may make an application to the 4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] for`
  line `granting immunity from penalty, if —`
  line `( a ) he has made an application for settlement under section 245C and the proceedings for`
  line `settlement have abated under section 245HA; and`
  line `( b ) the penalty proceedings have been initiated under this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) The application to the 4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] under sub-section ( 1 ) shall not`
  line `be made after the imposition of penalty after abatement.`
  line `( 3 ) The 4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] may, subject to such conditions as he may think`
  line `fit to impose, grant to the person immunity from the imposition of any penalty under this Act, if he is`
  line `satisfied that the person has, after the abatement, co-operated with the income-tax authority in the`
  line `proceedings before him and has made a full and true disclosure of his income and the manner in which`
  line `such income has been derived.`
  line `8 [( 3A ) The order under sub-section ( 3 ), either accepting or rejecting the application in full or in part,`
  line `shall be passed within a period of twelve months from the end of the month in which the application`
  line `under the said sub-section is received by the Principal Commissioner or the Commissioner:`
  line `Provided that no order rejecting the application, either in full or in part, shall be passed unless the`
  line `assessee has been given an opportunity of being heard:`
  line `Provided further that where any application is pending as on the 1st day of June, 2016, the order shall`
  line `be passed on or before the 31st day of May, 2017.]`
  line `( 4 ) The immunity granted to a person under sub-section ( 3 ) shall stand withdrawn, if such person fails`
  line `to comply with any condition subject to which the immunity was granted and thereupon the provisions of`
  line `this Act shall apply as if such immunity had not been granted.`
  line `( 5 ) The immunity granted to a person under sub-section ( 3 ) may, at any time, be withdrawn by the`
  line `4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner], if he is satisfied that such person had, in the course of any`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 113 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 51 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 48 (w.e.f. -6-1994).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
