obj_root_law_sections_799_content:
  string
  line 799
  line `1 [ 275. Bar of limitation for imposing penalties. — 2 [( 1 )] No order imposing a penalty under this`
  line `Chapter shall be passed —`
  line `3 [( a ) in a case where the relevant assessment or other order is the subject-matter of an appeal to`
  line `the 4 *** Commissioner (Appeals) under section 246 5 [or section 246A] or an appeal to the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal under section 253, after the expiry of the financial year in which the proceedings, in the`
  line `course of which action for the imposition of penalty has been initiated, are completed, or six months`
  line `from the end of the month in which the order of the 4 *** Commissioner (Appeals) or, as the case may`
  line `be, the Appellate Tribunal is received by the 6 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner]`
  line `or 7 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner], whichever period expires later:`
  line `8 [Provided that in a case where the relevant assessment or other order is the subject-matter of an`
  line `appeal to the Commissioner (Appeals) under section 246 or section 246A, and the Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals) passes the order on or after the 1st day of June, 2003 disposing of such appeal, an order`
  line `imposing penalty shall be passed before the expiry of the financial year in which the proceedings, in`
  line `the course of which action for imposition of penalty has been initiated, are completed, or within one`
  line `year from the end of the financial year in which the order of the Commissioner (Appeals) is received`
  line `by the 6 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 7 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner], whichever is later;]`
  line `( b ) in a case where the relevant assessment or other order is the subject-matter of revision`
  line `under section 263 8 [or section 264], after the expiry of six months from the end of the month in which`
  line `such order of revision is passed;`
  line `( c ) in any other case, after the expiry of the financial year in which the proceedings, in the course`
  line `of which action for the imposition of penalty has been initiated, are completed, or six months from`
  line `the end of the month in which action for imposition of penalty is initiated, whichever period expires`
  line later.]
  line `9 [( 1A ) In a case where the relevant assessment or other order is the subject-matter of an appeal to the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals) under section 246 or section 246A or an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `under section 253 or an appeal to the High Court under section 260A or an appeal to the Supreme Court`
  line `under section 261 or revision under section 263 or section 264 and an order imposing or enhancing or`
  line `reducing or cancelling penalty or dropping the proceedings for the imposition of penalty is passed before`
  line `the order of the Commissioner (Appeals) or the Appellate Tribunal or the High Court or the Supreme`
  line `Court is received by the 6 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or the 7 [Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner] or the order of revision under section 263 or section 264 is passed, an`
  line `order imposing or enhancing or reducing or cancelling penalty or dropping the proceedings for the`
  line `imposition of penalty may be passed on the basis of assessment as revised by giving effect to such order`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 50, for section 275 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `2. Section 275 renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 36 of 1989, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 116, for clauses ( a ) and ( b ) excluding the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. The words and brackets “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or the” omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 70 (w.e.f. 1-6-2000).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 96 (w.e.f. 1-6-2003).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 18 (w.e.f. 13-7-2006).`
