obj_root_law_sections_800_content:
  string
  line 800
  line `of the Commissioner (Appeals) or, the Appellate Tribunal or the High Court, or the Supreme Court or`
  line `order of revision under section 263 or section 264:`
  line `Provided that no order of imposing or enhancing or reducing or cancelling penalty or dropping the`
  line `proceedings for the imposition of penalty shall be passed —`
  line `( a ) unless the assessee has been heard, or has been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard;`
  line `( b ) after the expiry of six months from the end of the month in which the order of the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals) or the Appellate Tribunal or the High Court or the Supreme Court is`
  line `received by the 1 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or the 2 [Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner] or the order of revision under section 263 or section 264 is passed:`
  line `Provided further that the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 274 shall apply in respect of the`
  line `order imposing or enhancing or reducing penalty under this sub-section.]`
  line `3 [( 2 ) The provisions of this section as they stood immediately before their amendment by the Direct`
  line `Tax Laws (Amendment) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988), shall apply to and in relation to any action initiated for the`
  line `imposition of penalty on or before the 31st day of March, 1989.]`
  line `4 [ Explanation. — In computing the period of limitation for the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) the time taken in giving an opportunity to the assessee to be reheard under the proviso to`
  line `section 129;`
  line `( ii ) any period during which the immunity granted under section 245H remained in force; and`
  line `( iii ) any period during which a proceeding under this Chapter for the levy of penalty is stayed by`
  line `an order or injunction of any court,`
  line `shall be excluded.]]`
  line `CHAPTER XXII`
  line `O FFENCES AND PROSECUTIONS`
  line `5 [ 275A. Contravention of order made under sub-section ( 3 ) of section 132. — Whoever`
  line `contravenes any order referred to in 6 [the second proviso to sub-section ( 1 ) or] sub-section ( 3 ) of section`
  line `132 shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment which may extend to two years and shall also be`
  line `liable to fine.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 36 of 1989, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 66, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-1-1976).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 1 of 1965, s. 4 (w.e.f. 12-3-1965).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
