  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_801_footnotes
  sourcePage 801
obj_root_law_sections_801_content:
  string
  line 801
  line `1 [ 275B. Failure to comply with the provisions of clause ( iib ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 132. — If`
  line `a person who is required to afford the authorised officer the necessary facility to inspect the books of`
  line `account or other documents, as required under clause ( iib ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 132, fails to afford`
  line `such facility to the authorised officer, he shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to two years and shall also be liable to fine.]`
  line `2 [ 276. Removal, concealment, transfer or delivery of property to thwart tax recovery. — Whoever`
  line `fraudulently removes, conceals, transfers or delivers to any person, any property or any interest therein,`
  line `intending thereby to prevent that property or interest therein from being taken in execution of a certificate`
  line `under the provisions of the Second Schedule shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to two years and shall also be liable to fine.]`
  line `3 [ 276A. Failure to comply with the provisions of sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 3 ) of section 178. — If a`
  line `person 4 *** —`
  line `( i ) fails to give the notice in accordance with sub-section ( 1 ) of section 178; or`
  line `( ii ) fails to set aside the amount as required by sub-section ( 3 ) of that section; or`
  line `( iii ) parts with any of the assets of the company or the properties in his hands in contravention of`
  line `the provisions of the aforesaid sub-section,`
  line `he shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years:`
  line `Provided that in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be recorded in the`
  line `judgment of the court, such imprisonment shall not be for less than six months.]`
  line `276AA. [Failure to comply with the provisions of section 269AB or section 269-I]. — Omitted by`
  line `the Finance Act, 1986 (23 of 1986), s. 37 ( w.e.f. 1-10-1986). Original section was inserted by the Income-`
  line `tax ( Amendment ) Act, 1981 (22 of 1981), s. 10 ( w.e.f. 1-7-1982).`
  line `5 [ 276AB. Failure to comply with the provisions of sections 269UC, 269UE and 269UL. —`
  line `Whoever 4 *** fails to comply with the provisions of section 269UC or fails to surrender or deliver`
  line `possession of the property under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 269UE or contravenes the provisions of sub-`
  line `section ( 2 ) of section 269UL shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to two years and shall also be liable to fine:`
  line `Provided that in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be recorded in the`
  line `judgment of the court, such imprisonment shall not be for less than six months.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 107 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 117 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 58 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `4. The words “, without reasonable cause or excuse,” omitted by Act 46 of 1986, s. 27 (w.e.f. 10 -9-1986).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 23 of 1986, s. 36 (w.e.f. 13-5-1986).`
