obj_root_law_sections_802_content:
  string
  line 802
  line `1 [ 2 [276B. Failure to pay tax to the credit of Central Government under Chapter XII-D or`
  line `XVII-B. — If a person fails to pay to the credit of the Central Government, —`
  line `( a ) the tax deducted at source by him as required by or under the provisions of Chapter XVII-B;`
  line or
  line `( b ) the tax payable by him, as required by or under —`
  line `( i ) sub-section ( 2 ) of section 115-O; or`
  line `( ii ) the second proviso to section 194B,`
  line `he shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three months`
  line `but which may extend to seven years and with fine.]`
  line `3 [ 276BB. Failure to pay the tax collected at source. — If a person fails to pay to the credit of the`
  line `Central Government, the tax collected by him as required under the provisions of section 206C, he shall`
  line `be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three months but which`
  line `may extend to seven years and with fine.]`
  line `276C. Wilful attempt to evade tax, etc. — ( 1 ) If a person wilfully attempts in any manner whatsoever`
  line `to evade any tax, penalty or interest chargeable 4 [or imposable, or under reports his income, ] under this`
  line `Act, he shall, without prejudice to any penalty that may be imposable on him under any other provision of`
  line `this Act, be punishable, —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the amount sought to be evaded 5 [or tax on under-reported income] exceeds`
  line `6 [twenty-five hundred thousand rupees], with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be`
  line `less than six months but which may extend to seven years and with fine;`
  line `( ii ) in any other case, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three`
  line `months but which may extend to 7 [two years] and with fine.`
  line `( 2 ) If a person wilfully attempts in any manner whatsoever to evade the payment of any tax, penalty`
  line `or interest under this Act, he shall, without prejudice to any penalty that may be imposable on him under`
  line `any other provision of this Act, be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be`
  line `less than three months but which may extend to 8 [two years] and shall, in the discretion of the court, also`
  line `be liable to fine.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, a wilful attempt to evade any tax, penalty or interest`
  line `chargeable or imposable under this Act or the payment thereof shall include a case where any person —`
  line `( i ) has in his possession or control any books of account or other documents (being books of`
  line `account or other documents relevant to any proceeding under this Act) containing a false entry or`
  line `statement; or`
  line `( ii ) makes or causes to be made any false entry or statement in such books of account or other`
  line `documents; or`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 56, for section 276B (w.e.f. 1-6-1997).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 68, for section 276B and 276C (w.e.f. 1-10-1975). Earlier section 276C was inserted by Act`
  line `42 of 1970, s. 52 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971) and section 276B was inserted by Act 19 of 1968, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-1968) and later on`
  line `section 276B amended by Act 46 of 1986, s. 27 (w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 46 (w.e.f. 1-6-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 109, for “or imposable” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 109, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 106, for “one hundred thousand rupees” (w.e.f.1 -7-2012).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 106, ibid., for “three years” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
