obj_root_law_sections_803_content:
  string
  line 803
  line `( iii ) wilfully omits or causes to be omitted any relevant entry or statement in such books of`
  line `account or other documents; or`
  line `( iv ) causes any other circumstance to exist which will have the effect of enabling such person to`
  line `evade any tax, penalty or interest chargeable or imposable under this Act or the payment thereof.`
  line `276CC. Failure to furnish returns of income. — If a person wilfully fails to furnish in due time 1 [the`
  line `return of fringe benefits which he is required to furnish under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115WD or by`
  line `notice given under sub-section ( 2 ) of the said section or section 115WH or] the return of income which he`
  line `is required to furnish under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139 or by notice given under 2 [clause ( i ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 142] or 3 [section 148 or section 153A,] he shall be punishable, —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the amount of tax, which would have been evaded if the failure had not been`
  line `discovered, exceeds 4 [twenty-five hundred thousand rupees], with rigorous imprisonment for a term`
  line `which shall not be less than six months but which may extend to seven years and with fine;`
  line `( ii ) in any other case, with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three months but`
  line `which may extend to 5 [two years] and with fine:`
  line `Provided that a person shall not be proceeded against under this section for failure to furnish in`
  line `due time the 6 [return of fringe benefits under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 115WD or return of income`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 139] —`
  line `( i ) for any assessment year commencing prior to the 1st day of April, 1975; or`
  line `( ii ) for any assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 1975, if —`
  line `( a ) the return is furnished by him before the expiry of the assessment year; or`
  line `( b ) the 7 [tax payable by such person, not being a company,] on the total income`
  line `determined on regular assessment, as reduced by the advance tax, if any, paid, and any tax`
  line `deducted at source, does not exceed three thousand rupees.]]`
  line `8 [ 276CCC. Failure to furnish return of income in search cases. — If a person wilfully fails to`
  line `furnish in due time the return of total income which he is required to furnish by notice given under clause`
  line `( a ) of section 158BC, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than`
  line `three months but which may extend to three years and with fine:`
  line `Provided that no person shall be punishable for any failure under this section in respect of search`
  line `initiated under section 132 or books of account, other documents or any assets requisitioned under`
  line `section 132A, after the 30th day of June, 1995 but before the 1st day of January, 1997.]`
  line `9 [ 276D. Failure to produce accounts and documents. — If a person wilfully fails to produce, or`
  line `cause to be produced, on or before the date specified in any notice served on him under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 142, such accounts and documents as are referred to in the notice 10 [or wilfully fails to comply`
  line `with a direction issued to him under sub-section ( 2A ) of that section], he shall be punishable with rigorous`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year 11 [and with fine].]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 62 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 126, for “sub -section ( 2 ) of section 139” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 97, for “section 148” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2003).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 107, “one hundred thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 107, ibid., for “three years” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 18 of 200 5, s. 62, for “return of income under sub -section ( 1 ) of section 139” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 54, for “tax payable by him” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2018).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 14 of 1997, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-1-1997).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 52 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 69 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 74, for “or with fine equal to a sum calculated at a rate which shall not be less than four`
  line `rupees or more than ten rupees for every day during which the default continues, or with both “ (w.e.f. 1 -10-2014).`
