obj_root_law_sections_804_content:
  string
  line 804
  line `276DD. [Failure to comply with the provisions of section 269SS]. — Omitted by the Direct Tax`
  line `Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1987 (4 of 1987), s. 119 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier it was inserted by the Finance`
  line `Act (21 of 1984), s. 31 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1984) and later on amended by the Taxation Laws (Amendments and`
  line `Miscellaneous Provisions ) Act (46 of 1986), s. 27 ( w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
  line `276E. [Failure to comply with the provisions of section 269T]. — Omitted by s. 119, ibid.,`
  line `( w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier it was inserted by the Income-Tax ( Second Amendment ) Act (38 of 1981), s. 4`
  line `( w.e.f. 11-7-1981) and later on amended by the Taxation Laws (Amendments and Miscellaneous`
  line `Provisions ) Act (46 of 1986), s. 27 ( w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
  line `1 [ 277. False statement in verification, etc. — If a person makes a statement in any verification under`
  line `this Act or under any rule made thereunder, or delivers an account or statement which is false, and which`
  line `he either knows or believes to be false, or does not believe to be true, he shall be punishable, —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the amount of tax, which would have been evaded if the statement or account`
  line `had been accepted as true, exceeds 2 [twenty-five hundred thousand rupees], with rigorous`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months but which may extend to seven years`
  line `and with fine;`
  line `( ii ) in any other case, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three`
  line `months but which may extend to 3 [two years] and with fine.`
  line `4 [ 277A. Falsification of books of account or document, etc. — If any person (hereafter in this`
  line `section referred to as the first person) wilfully and with intent to enable any other person (hereafter in this`
  line `section referred to as the second person) to evade any tax or interest or penalty chargeable and imposable`
  line `under this Act, makes or causes to be made any entry or statement which is false and which the first`
  line `person either knows to be false or does not believe to be true, in any books of account or other document`
  line `relevant to or useful in any proceedings against the first person or the second person, under this Act, the`
  line `first person shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three`
  line `months but which may extend to 5 [two years] and with fine.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of establishing the charge under this section, it shall not be necessary`
  line `to prove that the second person has actually evaded any tax, penalty or interest chargeable or imposable`
  line `under this Act.]`
  line `278. Abetment of false return, etc. — If a person abets or induces in any manner another person to`
  line `make and deliver an account or a statement or declaration relating to 6 [any income or any fringe benefits`
  line `chargeable to tax] which is false and which he either knows to be false or does not believe to be true or to`
  line `commit an offence under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 276C, he shall be punishable, —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the amount of tax, penalty or interest which would have been evaded, if the`
  line `declaration, account or statement had been accepted as true, or which is wilfully attempted to be`
  line `evaded, exceeds 7 [twenty-five hundred thousand rupees], with rigorous imprisonment for a term`
  line `which shall not be less than six months but which may extend to seven years and with fine;`
  line `( ii ) in any other case, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three`
  line `months but which may extend to 8 [two years] and with fine.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 70, for sections 277 and 278 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 108, for “one hundred thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 108, ibid., for “three years” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 60 (w.e.f. 1-10-2004).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 109, for “three years” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 63, for “any income chargeable to tax” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2006).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 110, for “one hundred thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 110, ibid., for “three years” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
