obj_root_law_sections_805_content:
  string
  line 805
  line `278A. Punishment for second and subsequent offences. — If any person convicted of an offence`
  line `under section 276B or sub-section ( 1 ) of section 276C or section 276CC 1 [or section 276DD]`
  line `2 [or section 276E] or section 277 or section 278 is again convicted of an offence under any of the`
  line `aforesaid provisions, he shall be punishable for the second and for every subsequent offence with rigorous`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months but which may extend to seven years and`
  line `with fine.`
  line `3 [ 278AA. Punishment not to be imposed in certain cases. — Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `the provisions of section 276A, section 276AB, 4 [or section 276B,] no person shall be punishable for any`
  line `failure referred to in the said provisions if he proves that there was reasonable cause for such failure.]`
  line `5 [ 278AB. Power of 6 [ Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] to grant immunity from`
  line `prosecution. — ( 1 ) A person may make an application to the 6 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]`
  line `for granting immunity from prosecution, if he has made an application for settlement under section`
  line `245C and the proceedings for settlement have abated under section 245HA.`
  line `( 2 ) The application to the 6 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] under sub-section ( 1 ) shall not`
  line `be made after institution of the prosecution proceedings after abatement.`
  line `( 3 ) The 6 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] may, subject to such conditions as he may think`
  line `fit to impose, grant to the person immunity from prosecution for any offence under this Act, if he is`
  line `satisfied that the person has, after the abatement, co-operated with the income-tax authority in the`
  line `proceedings before him and has made a full and true disclosure of his income and the manner in which`
  line `such income has been derived:`
  line `Provided that where the application for settlement under section 245C had been made before the 1st`
  line `day of June, 2007, the 6 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] may grant immunity from prosecution`
  line `for any offence under this Act or under the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) or under any other Central Act`
  line `for the time being in force.`
  line `( 4 ) The immunity granted to a person under sub-section ( 3 ) shall stand withdrawn, if such person fails`
  line `to comply with any condition subject to which the immunity was granted and thereupon the provisions of`
  line `this Act shall apply as if such immunity had not been granted.`
  line `( 5 ) The immunity granted to a person under sub-section ( 3 ) may, at any time, be withdrawn by`
  line `the 6 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner], if he is satisfied that such person had, in the course of`
  line `any proceedings, after abatement, concealed any particulars material to the assessment from the`
  line `income-tax authority or had given false evidence, and thereupon such person may be tried for the offence`
  line `with respect to which the immunity was granted or for any other offence of which he appears to have`
  line `been guilty in connection with the proceedings.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 1985, s. 35 (w.e.f. 24-5-1985).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 38 of 1981, s. 5 (w.e.f. 11-7-1981).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 28 (w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 120, for “section 276B, section 276DD or section 276E” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 54 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Commissioner” ( w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
