obj_root_law_sections_806_content:
  string
  line 806
  line `278B. Offences by companies. — ( 1 ) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company as well as the company shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line `1 [( 3 ) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a person, being a company, and the`
  line `punishment for such offence is imprisonment and fine, then, without prejudice to the provisions contained`
  line `in sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ), such company shall be punished with fine and every person, referred`
  line `to in sub-section ( 1 ), or the director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company referred to in sub-`
  line `section ( 2 ), shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished in accordance with the provisions of this`
  line Act.]
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “company” means a body corporate, and includes—`
  line `( i ) a firm; and`
  line `( ii ) an association of persons or a body of individuals whether incorporated or not; and`
  line `( b ) “director”, in relation to—`
  line `( i ) a firm, means a partner in the firm;`
  line `( ii ) any association of persons or a body of individuals, means any member controlling the`
  line `affairs thereof.`
  line `278C. Offences by Hindu undivided families. — ( 1 ) Where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a Hindu undivided family, the karta thereof shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and`
  line `shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render the karta liable to any punishment if`
  line `he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised all due`
  line `diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), where an offence under this Act, has been`
  line `committed by a Hindu undivided family and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the`
  line `consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any member of the Hindu`
  line `undivided family, such member shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be`
  line `proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 61 (w.e.f. 1-10-2004).`
