obj_root_law_sections_807_content:
  string
  line 807
  line `278D. Presumption as to assets, books of account, etc., in certain cases. — ( 1 ) Where during the`
  line `course of any search made under section 132, any money, bullion, jewellery or other valuable article or`
  line `thing (hereafter in this section referred to as the assets) or any books of account or other documents has or`
  line `have been found in the possession or control of any person and such assets or books of account or other`
  line `documents are tendered by the prosecution in evidence against such person or against such person and the`
  line `person referred to in section 278 for an offence under this Act, the provisions of sub-section ( 4A )`
  line `of section 132shall, so far as may be, apply in relation to such assets or books of account or other`
  line documents.
  line `( 2 ) Where any assets or books of account or other documents taken into custody, from the possession`
  line `or control of any person, by the officer or authority referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ), as`
  line `the case may be, of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 132A are delivered to the requisitioning officer under sub-`
  line `section ( 2 ) of that section and such assets, books of account or other documents are tendered by the`
  line `prosecution in evidence against such person or against such person and the person referred to in section`
  line `278 for an offence under this Act, the provisions of sub-section ( 4A ) of section 132 shall, so far as may`
  line `be, apply in relation to such assets or books of account or other documents.]`
  line `1 [ 278E. Presumption as to culpable mental state. — ( 1 ) In any prosecution for any offence under`
  line `this Act which requires a culpable mental state on the part of the accused, the court shall presume the`
  line `existence of such mental state but it shall be a defence for the accused to prove the fact that he had no`
  line `such mental state with respect to the act charged as an offence in that prosecution.`
  line `Explanation. — In this sub- section, “culpable mental state” includes intention, motive or knowledge of`
  line `a fact or belief in, or reason to believe, a fact.`
  line `( 2 ) For the purposes of this section, a fact is said to be proved only when the court believes it to exist`
  line `beyond reasonable doubt and not merely when its existence is established by a preponderance of`
  line probability.]
  line `279. Prosecution to be at instance of 2 [ 3 [ Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner]`
  line `or 4 [ Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]]. — 5 [( 1 ) A person shall not be proceeded against for an`
  line `offence under section 275A, 6 [ section 275B,] section 276, section 276A, section 276B, section`
  line `276BB, section 276C, section 276CC,section 276D, 7 [section 277, section 277A or section 278] except`
  line `with the previous sanction of the 4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] or Commissioner (Appeals)`
  line `or the appropriate authority:`
  line `Provided that the 3 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or, as the case may be,`
  line `8 [Principal Director General or Director] General may issue such instructions or directions to the`
  line `aforesaid income-tax authorities as he may deem fit for institution of proceedings under this sub-section.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, “appropriate authority” shall have the same meaning`
  line `as in clause ( c ) of section 269UA.]`
  line `( 1A ) A person shall not be proceeded against for an offence under section 276C or section 277 in`
  line `relation to the assessment for an assessment year in respect of which the penalty imposed or imposable on`
  line `him under 9 [section 270A or] clause ( iii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 271 has been reduced or waived by`
  line `an order under section 273A.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 29 (w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 70, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 108 (w.e.f 1-6-2002).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 62, for “section 277 of section 278” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2004).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Director General” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
