obj_root_law_sections_808_content:
  string
  line 808
  line `1 [( 2 ) Any offence under this Chapter may, either before or after the institution of proceedings, be`
  line `compounded by the 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or a 3 [Principal Director`
  line `General or Director General].`
  line `4 [( 3 ) Where any proceeding has been taken against any person under sub-section ( 1 ), any statement`
  line `made or account or other document produced by such person before any of the income-tax authorities`
  line `specified in 5 [clauses ( a ) to ( g )] of section 116 shall not be inadmissible as evidence for the purpose of`
  line `such proceedings merely on the ground that such statement was made or such account or other document`
  line `was produced in the belief that the penalty imposable would be reduced or waived, 6 [under section`
  line `273A] or that the offence in respect of which such proceeding was taken would be compounded.`
  line `7 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the power of the Board to issue`
  line `orders, instructions or directions under this Act shall include and shall be deemed always to have included`
  line `the power to issue instructions or directions (including instructions or directions to obtain the previous`
  line `approval of the Board) to other income-tax authorities for the proper composition of offences under this`
  line section.]
  line `8 [ 279A. Certain offences to be non-cognizable. — Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code`
  line `of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), an offence punishable under section 276B or section`
  line `276C or section 276CC or section 277 or section 278 shall be deemed to be non-cognizable within the`
  line `meaning of that Code.]`
  line `9 [ 279B. Proof of entries in records or documents. — Entries in the records or other documents in the`
  line `custody of an income-tax authority shall be admitted in evidence in any proceedings for the prosecution`
  line `of any person for an offence under this Chapter, and all such entries may be proved either by the`
  line `production of the records or other documents in the custody of the income-tax authority containing such`
  line `entries, or by the production of a copy of the entries certified by the income-tax authority having custody`
  line `of the records or other documents under its signature and stating that it is a true copy of the original`
  line `entries and that such original entries are contained in the records or other documents in its custody.]`
  line `280. Disclosure of particulars by public servants. — ( 1 ) If a public servant 10 [furnishes any`
  line `information or produces any document in contravention of the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) of section`
  line `138], he shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to six months, and shall also be liable`
  line `to fine.`
  line `( 2 ) No prosecution shall be instituted under this section except with the previous sanction of the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line `11 [ 280A. Special Courts. — ( 1 ) The Central Government, in consultation with the Chief Justice of the`
  line `High Court, may, for trial of offences punishable under this Chapter, by notification, designate one or`
  line `more courts of Magistrate of the first class as Special Court for such area or areas or for such cases or`
  line `class or group of cases as may be specified in the notification.`
  line `Explanation. — In this sub- section, “High Court” means the High Court of the State in which a`
  line `Magistrate of first class designated as Special Court was functioning immediately before such`
  line designation.
  line `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 70 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991). Earlier substituted by Act 26of 1988, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Director General” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 1 of 1965, s. 5 (w.e.f. 12-3-1965).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 126, for “ clauses ( a ), ( b ), ( c ), ( d ) and ( e )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 71, for “under sub -section ( 4A ) of section 271” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1975).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 70 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 72 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 53 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `10.Subs. by Act 5 of 1964, s. 43, for “discioses any particulars, the disclosure of which is prohibited by section 137,”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1964).`
  line `11. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 111 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_808_footnotes:
