obj_root_law_sections_809_content:
  string
  line 809
  line `( 2 ) While trying an offence under this Act, a Special Court shall also try an offence, other than an`
  line `offence referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), with which the accused may, under the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), be charged at the same trial.`
  line `280B. Offences triable by Special Court. — Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), —`
  line `( a ) the offences punishable under this Chapter shall be triable only by the Special Court, if so`
  line `designated, for the area or areas or for cases or class or group of cases, as the case may be, in which`
  line `the offence has been committed:`
  line `Provided that a court competent to try offences under section 292, —`
  line `( i ) which has been designated as a Special Court under this section, shall continue to try the`
  line `offences before it or offences arising under this Act after such designation;`
  line `( ii ) which has not been designated as a Special Court may continue to try such offence`
  line `pending before it till its disposal;`
  line `( b ) a Special Court may, upon a complaint made by an authority authorised in this behalf under`
  line `this Act take cognizance of the offence for which the accused is committed for trial.`
  line `280C. Trial of offences as summons case. — Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), the Special Court, shall try, an offence under this Chapter`
  line `punishable with imprisonment not exceeding two years or with fine or with both, as a summons case, and`
  line `the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 as applicable in the case of trial of summons case,`
  line `shall apply accordingly.`
  line `280D. Application of Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 to proceedings before Special`
  line `Court. — ( 1 ) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure,`
  line `1973 (2 of 1974) (including the provisions as to bails or bonds), shall apply to the proceedings before a`
  line `Special Court and the person conducting the prosecution before the Special Court, shall be deemed to be a`
  line `Public Prosecutor:`
  line `Provided that the Central Government may also appoint for any case or class or group of cases a`
  line `Special Public Prosecutor.`
  line `( 2 ) A person shall not be qualified to be appointed as a Public Prosecutor or a Special Public`
  line `Prosecutor under this section unless he has been in practice as an advocate for not less than seven years,`
  line `requiring special knowledge of law.`
  line `( 3 ) Every person appointed as a Public Prosecutor or a Special Public Prosecutor under this section`
  line `shall be deemed to be a Public Prosecutor within the meaning of clause ( u ) of section 2 of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) and the provisions of that Code shall have effect accordingly.]`
  line `280E. CHAPTER XXII-A dealing with Annuity Deposits containing sections 280A to 280X were`
  line `omitted by Finance Act, 1988 (26 of 1988), s. 48 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988). Sections 280A to 280D were`
  line `subsequently inserted by Act 23 of 2012, s. 111 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `[CHAPTER XXII-B TAX CREDIT CERTIFICATES]. — Omitted by the Finance Act, 1990 (12 of`
  line `1990), s. 48 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `[280Y. Definitions]. — Omitted by s. 48, ibid. ( w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `[280Z. Tax credit certificates to certain equity shareholders]. — Omitted by s. 48, ibid.`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `[280ZA. Tax credit certificates for shifting of industrial undertaking from urban area]. —`
  line `Omitted by the Finance Act, 1987 (11 of 1987), s. 70 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988). Original section was inserted by`
  line `the Finance Act, 1965 (10 of 1965), s. 62 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `[280ZB. Tax credit certificate to certain manufacturing companies in certain cases]. — Omitted`
  line `by the Finance Act, 1990 ( 12 of 1990 ), s. 48 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `[280ZC. Tax credit certificate in relation to exports]. — Omitted by s. 48, ibid. ( w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `[280ZD. Tax credit certificates in relation to increased production of certain goods]. — Omitted`
  line `by the s. 48, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1990 ).`
  line `[280ZE. Tax credit certificate scheme ]. — Omitted by s. 48, ibid. ( w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
obj_root_law_sections_809_footnotes:
