  content obj_root_law_sections_810_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_810_footnotes
  sourcePage 810
obj_root_law_sections_810_content:
  string
  line 810
  line `CHAPTER XXIII`
  line `M ISCELLANEOUS`
  line `1 [ 281. Certain transfers to be void. — ( 1 ) Where, during the pendency of any proceeding under this`
  line `Act or after the completion thereof, but before the service of notice under rule 2 of the Second Schedule,`
  line `any assessee creates a charge on, or parts with the possession (by way of sale, mortgage, gift, exchange or`
  line `any other mode of transfer whatsoever) of, any of his assets in favour of any other person, such charge or`
  line `transfer shall be void as against any claim in respect of any tax or any other sum payable by the assessee`
  line `as a result of the completion of the said proceeding or otherwise:`
  line `Provided that such charge or transfer shall not be void if it is made —`
  line `( i ) for adequate consideration and without notice of the pendency of such proceeding or, as the`
  line `case may be, without notice of such tax or other sum payable by the assessee; or`
  line `( ii ) with the previous permission of the 2 [Assessing Officer].`
  line `( 2 ) This section applies to cases where the amount of tax or other sum payable or likely to be payable`
  line `exceeds five thousand rupees and the assets charged or transferred exceed ten thousand rupees in value.`
  line `Explanation. —In this section, “assets” means land, building, machinery, plant, shares, securities and`
  line `fixed deposits in banks, to the extent to which any of the assets aforesaid does not form part of the`
  line `stock-in-trade of the business of the assessee.]`
  line `281A. [Effect of failure to furnish information in respect of properties held benami]. — Rep. by`
  line `the Benami Transactions ( Prohibition ) Act, 1988 (46 of 1988), s. 7 ( w.e.f. 19-5-1988).`
  line `3 [ 281B. Provisional attachment to protect revenue in certain cases. — ( 1 ) Where, during the`
  line `pendency of any proceeding for the assessment of any income or for the assessment or reassessment of`
  line `any income which has escaped assessment, the 2 [Assessing Officer] is of the opinion that for the purpose`
  line `of protecting the interests of the revenue it is necessary so to do, he may, with the previous approval of`
  line `the 4 [ 5 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner], 6 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner], 7 [Principal Director General or Director General] or 8 [Principal Director or Director]], by`
  line `order in writing, attach provisionally any property belonging to the assessee in the manner provided in the`
  line `Second Schedule.`
  line `9 * * * * *`
  line `( 2 ) Every such provisional attachment shall cease to have effect after the expiry of a period of six`
  line `months from the date of the order made under sub-section ( 1 ):`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 73, for section 281 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 74 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 57, for “Chief Commissioner or Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10- 1996). Earlier “Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner” was substituted for “Commissioner” by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Director General” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Director” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `9. The Explanation omitted by Act 28 of 2016, s. 111 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_810_footnotes:
