  line
obj_root_law_sections_811:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-811
  sectionNo (811)
  orderNo 811
  title `Page 811`
  content obj_root_law_sections_811_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_811_footnotes
  sourcePage 811
obj_root_law_sections_811_content:
  string
  line 811
  line `Provided that the 1 [ 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner], 3 [Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner], 4 [Principal Director General or Director General] or 5 [Principal`
  line `Director or Director]] may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, extend the aforesaid period by such`
  line `further period or periods as he thinks fit, so, however, that the total period of extension shall not in any`
  line `case exceed 6 [two years or sixty days after the date of order of assessment or reassessment, whichever is`
  line later].]
  line `7 * * * * *`
  line `8 [( 3 ) Where the assessee furnishes a guarantee from a scheduled bank for an amount not less than the`
  line `fair market value of the property provisionally attached under sub-section ( 1 ), the Assessing Officer shall,`
  line `by an order in writing, revoke such attachment:`
  line `Provided that where the Assessing Officer is satisfied that a guarantee from a scheduled bank for an`
  line `amount lower than the fair market value of the property is sufficient to protect the interests of the revenue,`
  line `he may accept such guarantee and revoke the attachment.`
  line `( 4 ) The Assessing Officer may, for the purposes of determining the value of the property`
  line `provisionally attached under sub-section ( 1 ), make a reference to the Valuation Officer referred to`
  line `in section 142A, who shall estimate the fair market value of the property in the manner provided under`
  line `that section and submit a report of the estimate to the Assessing Officer within a period of thirty days`
  line `from the date of receipt of such reference.`
  line `( 5 ) An order revoking the provisional attachment under sub-section ( 3 ) shall be made —`
  line `( i ) within forty-five days from the date of receipt of the guarantee, where a reference to the`
  line `Valuation Officer has been made under sub-section ( 4 ); or`
  line `( ii ) within fifteen days from the date of receipt of guarantee in any other case.`
  line `( 6 ) Where a notice of demand specifying a sum payable is served upon the assessee and the assessee`
  line `fails to pay that sum within the time specified in the notice of demand, the Assessing Officer may invoke`
  line `the guarantee furnished under sub-section ( 3 ), wholly or in part, to recover the amount.`
  line `( 7 ) The Assessing Officer shall, in the interests of the revenue, invoke the bank guarantee, if the`
  line `assessee fails to renew the guarantee referred to in sub-section ( 3 ), or fails to furnish a new guarantee`
  line `from a scheduled bank for an equal amount, fifteen days before the expiry of the guarantee referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ).`
  line `( 8 ) The amount realised by invoking the guarantee referred to in sub-section ( 3 ) shall be adjusted`
  line `against the existing demand which is payable by the assessee and the balance amount, if any, shall be`
  line `deposited in the Personal Deposit Account of the Principal Commissioner or Commissioner in the branch`
  line `of the Reserve Bank of India or the State Bank of India or of its subsidiaries or any bank as may be`
  line `appointed by the Reserve Bank of India as its agent under the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 45`
  line `of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934) at the place where the office of the Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner is situate.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 57, for “Chief Commissioner or Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10- 1996). Earlier “Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner” was substituted for “Commissioner” by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Director General” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Director” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 75, ibid., for “two years” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2014).`
  line `7. The Second and third proviso omitted by s. 75, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 111 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_811_footnotes:
