  title `Page 812`
  content obj_root_law_sections_812_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_812_footnotes
  sourcePage 812
obj_root_law_sections_812_content:
  string
  line 812
  line `( 9 ) Where the Assessing Officer is satisfied that the guarantee referred to in sub-section ( 3 ) is not`
  line `required any more to protect the interests of the revenue, he shall release that guarantee forthwith.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, the expression “scheduled bank” shall mean a bank`
  line `included in the Second Schedule to the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934).]`
  line `1 [ 282. Service of notice generally. — ( 1 ) The service of a notice or summon or requisition or order or`
  line `any other communication under this Act (hereafter in this section referred to as “communication”) may be`
  line `made by delivering or transmitting a copy thereof, to the person therein named, —`
  line `( a ) by post or by such courier services as may be approved by the Board; or`
  line `( b ) in such manner as provided under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) for the`
  line `purposes of service of summons; or`
  line `( c ) in the form of any electronic record as provided in Chapter IV of the Information Technology`
  line `Act, 2000 (21 of 2000); or`
  line `( d ) by any other means of transmission of documents as provided by rules made by the Board in`
  line `this behalf.`
  line `( 2 ) The Board may make rules providing for the addresses (including the address for electronic mail`
  line `or electronic mail message) to which the communication referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) may be delivered`
  line `or transmitted to the person therein named.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this section, the expressions “electronic mail” and “electronic mail`
  line `message” sha ll have the meanings as assigned to them in Explanation to section 66A of the Information`
  line `Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000).]`
  line `2 [ 282A. Authentication of notices and other documents. — ( 1 ) Where this Act requires a notice or`
  line `other document to be issued by any income-tax authority, such notice or other document shall be 3 [signed`
  line `and issued in paper form or communicated in electronic form by that authority in accordance with such`
  line `procedure as may be prescribed].`
  line `( 2 ) Every notice or other document to be issued, served or given for the purposes of this Act by any`
  line `income-tax authority, shall be deemed to be authenticated if the name and office of a designated`
  line `income-tax authority is printed, stamped or otherwise written thereon.`
  line `( 3 ) For the purposes of this section, a designated income-tax authority shall mean any income-tax`
  line `authority authorised by the Board to issue, serve or give such notice or other document after`
  line `authentication in the manner as provided in sub-section ( 2 ).]`
  line `282B. [Allotment of Document Identification Number]. — Omitted by the Finance Act, 2011`
  line `(8 of 2011), s. 31 ( w.e.f. 1-4-2011).`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 77, for section 282 (w.e.f. 1-10-2009).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 55 (w.e.f. 1-6-2008).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 112, for “signed in manuscript by that authority” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_812_footnotes:
  string
