  title `Page 813`
  content obj_root_law_sections_813_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_813_footnotes
  sourcePage 813
obj_root_law_sections_813_content:
  string
  line 813
  line `283. Service of notice when family is disrupted or firm, etc., is dissolved. — ( 1 ) After a finding of`
  line `total partition has been recorded by the 1 [Assessing Officer] under section 171 in respect of any Hindu`
  line `family, notices under this Act in respect of the income of the Hindu family shall be served on the person`
  line `who was the last manager of the Hindu family, or, if such person is dead, then on all adults who were`
  line `members of the Hindu family immediately before the partition.`
  line `( 2 ) Where a firm or other association of persons is dissolved, notices under this Act in respect of the`
  line `income of the firm or association may be served on any person who was a partner (not being a minor) or`
  line `member of the association, as the case may be, immediately before its dissolution.`
  line `284. Service of notice in the case of discontinued business. — Where an assessment is to be made`
  line `under section 176, the Assessing Officer may serve on the person whose income is to be assessed, or, in`
  line `the case of a firm or an association of persons, on any person who was a member of such firm or`
  line `association at the time of its discontinuance or, in the case of a company, on the principal officer thereof,`
  line `a notice containing all or any of the requirements which may be included in a notice under sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 139, and the provisions of this Act shall, so far as may be, apply accordingly as if the notice`
  line `were a notice issued under that section.`
  line `2 [ 285. Submission of statement by a non-resident having liaison office. — Every person, being a`
  line `non-resident having a liaison office in India set up in accordance with the guidelines issued by the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India under the Foreign Exchange Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999), shall, in respect`
  line `of its activities in a financial year, prepare and deliver or cause to be delivered to the Assessing Officer`
  line `having jurisdiction, within sixty days from the end of such financial year, a statement in such form and`
  line `containing such particulars as may be prescribed.]`
  line `3 [ 285A. Furnishing of information or documents by an Indian concern in certain cases. —`
  line `Where any share of, or interest in, a company or an entity registered or incorporated outside India derives,`
  line `directly or indirectly, its value substantially from the assets located in India, as referred to in Explanation`
  line `5 to clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 9, and such company or, as the case may be, entity, holds,`
  line `directly or indirectly, such assets in India through, or in, an Indian concern, then, such Indian concern`
  line `shall, for the purposes of determination of any income accruing or arising in India under clause ( i ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 9, furnish within the prescribed period to the prescribed income-tax authority`
  line `the information or documents, in such manner, as may be prescribed.]`
  line `4 [ 285B. Submission of statements by producers of cinematograph films. — Any person carrying on`
  line `the production of a cinematograph film during the whole or any part of any financial year shall, in respect`
  line `of the period during which such production is carried on by him in such financial year, prepare and`
  line `deliver or cause to be delivered to the 1 [Assessing Officer], within thirty days from the end of such`
  line `financial year or within thirty days from the date of the completion of the production of the film,`
  line `whichever is earlier, a statement in the prescribed form containing particulars of all payments of over`
  line `5 [fifty thousand rupees] in the aggregate made by him or due from him to each such person as is engaged`
  line `by him in such production 6 ***.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-6-2011). Earlier it was omitted by Act 11 of 1987, s. 71, (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 78 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016). Earlier it was inserted by Act 31 of 1964, s. 18, (w.e.f. 6-10-1964) and`
  line `later amended by the Act 41 of 1975, s. 76, (w.e.f. 1-4-1976). And then omitted by 26 of 1988, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 76 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 71, for “twenty - five thousand rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2001). Earlier it was subs. by Act 21 of`
  line `1998, s. 63, (w.e.f. 1-4-1999).`
  line `6. The words “as employee or otherwise” omitted by Act 13 of 1989, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1 -6-1989).`
