  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_814_footnotes
  sourcePage 814
obj_root_law_sections_814_content:
  string
  line 814
  line `1 [ 285BA. Obligation to furnish statement of financial transaction or reportable account. —`
  line `( 1 ) Any person, being —`
  line `( a ) an assessee; or`
  line `( b ) the prescribed person in the case of an office of Government; or`
  line `( c ) a local authority or other public body or association; or`
  line `( d ) the Registrar or Sub-Registrar appointed under section 6 of the Registration Act, 1908 (16`
  line `of 1908); or`
  line `( e ) the registering authority empowered to register motor vehicles under Chapter IV of the`
  line `Motor Vehicles Act, 1988 (59 of 1988); or`
  line `( f ) the Post Master General as referred to in clause ( j ) of section 2 of the Indian Post Office`
  line `Act, 1898 (6 of 1898); or`
  line `( g ) the Collector referred to in clause ( g ) of section 3 of the Right to Fair Compensation and`
  line `Transparency in Land Acquisition, Rehabilitation and Resettlement Act, 2013 (30 of 2013); or`
  line `( h ) the recognised stock exchange referred to in clause ( f ) of section 2 of the Securities`
  line `Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956); or`
  line `( i ) an officer of the Reserve Bank of India, constituted under section 3 of the Reserve Bank of`
  line `India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934); or`
  line `( j ) a depository referred to in clause ( e ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 2 of the Depositories`
  line `Act, 1996 (22 of 1996); or`
  line `( k ) a prescribed reporting financial institution,`
  line `who is responsible for registering, or, maintaining books of account or other document containing a`
  line `record of any specified financial transaction or any reportable account as may be prescribed, under any`
  line `law for the time being in force, shall furnish a statement in respect of such specified financial transaction`
  line `or such reportable account which is registered or recorded or maintained by him and information relating`
  line `to which is relevant and required for the purposes of this Act, to the income-tax authority or such other`
  line `authority or agency as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 2 ) The statement referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be furnished for such period, within such time`
  line `and in the form and manner, as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 3 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), “specified financial transaction” means any—`
  line `( a ) transaction of purchase, sale or exchange of goods or property or right or interest in a`
  line `property; or`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 76, for “section 285BA” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2015). Earlier inserted by Act 32 of 2003, s. 98,`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-2005) and later on subs. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 63 (w.e.f. 1-4-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_814_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_815:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-815
  sectionNo (815)
  orderNo 815
  title `Page 815`
  content obj_root_law_sections_815_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_815_footnotes
  sourcePage 815
obj_root_law_sections_815_content:
  string
  line 815
  line `( b ) transaction for rendering any service; or`
  line `( c ) transaction under a works contract; or`
  line `( d ) transaction by way of an investment made or an expenditure incurred; or`
  line `( e ) transaction for taking or accepting any loan or deposit,`
  line `which may be prescribed:`
  line `Provided that the Board may prescribe different values for different transactions in respect of`
  line `different persons having regard to the nature of such transaction:`
  line `Provided further that the value or, as the case may be, the aggregate value of such transactions during`
  line `a financial year so prescribed shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees.`
  line `( 4 ) Where the prescribed income-tax authority considers that the statement furnished under sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ) is defective, he may intimate the defect to the person who has furnished such statement and`
  line `give him an opportunity of rectifying the defect within a period of thirty days from the date of such`
  line `intimation or within such further period which, on an application made in this behalf, the said income-tax`
  line `authority may, in his discretion, allow; and if the defect is not rectified within the said period of thirty`
  line `days or, as the case may be, the further period so allowed, then, notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `any other provision of this Act, such statement shall be treated as an invalid statement and the provisions`
  line `of this Act shall apply as if such person had failed to furnish the statement.`
  line `( 5 ) Where a person who is required to furnish a statement under sub-section ( 1 ) has not furnished the`
  line `same within the specified time, the prescribed income-tax authority may serve upon such person a notice`
  line `requiring him to furnish such statement within a period not exceeding thirty days from the date of service`
  line `of such notice and he shall furnish the statement within the time specified in the notice.`
  line `( 6 ) If any person, having furnished a statement under sub-section ( 1 ), or in pursuance of a notice`
  line `issued under sub-section ( 5 ), comes to know or discovers any inaccuracy in the information provided in`
  line `the statement, he shall within a period of ten days inform the income-tax authority or other authority or`
  line `agency referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), the inaccuracy in such statement and furnish the correct information`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 7 ) The Central Government may, by rules made under this section, specify —`
  line `( a ) the persons referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) to be registered with the prescribed income-tax`
  line authority;
  line `( b ) the nature of information and the manner in which such information shall be maintained by`
  line `the persons referred to in clause ( a ); and`
  line `( c ) the due diligence to be carried out by the persons for the purpose of identification of any`
  line `reportable account referred to in sub-section ( 1 ).]`
obj_root_law_sections_815_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_816:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-816
