  content obj_root_law_sections_816_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_816_footnotes
  sourcePage 816
obj_root_law_sections_816_content:
  string
  line 816
  line `1 [ 286. Furnishing of report in respect of international group. — ( 1 ) Every constituent entity`
  line `resident in India, shall, if it is constituent of an international group, the parent entity of which is not`
  line `resident in India, notify the prescribed income-tax authority (herein referred to as prescribed authority) in`
  line `the form and manner, on or before such date, as may be prescribed, —`
  line `( a ) whether it is the alternate reporting entity of the international group; or`
  line `( b ) the details of the parent entity or the alternate reporting entity, if any, of the international`
  line `group, and the country or territory of which the said entities are resident.`
  line `( 2 ) Every parent entity or the alternate reporting entity, resident in India, shall, for every reporting`
  line `accounting year, in respect of the international group of which it is a constituent, furnish a report, to the`
  line `prescribed authority 2 [within a period of twelve months from the end of the said reporting accounting`
  line `year], in the form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 3 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 2 ) 3 [and sub-section ( 4 )], the report in respect of an international`
  line `group shall include, —`
  line `( a ) the aggregate information in respect of the amount of revenue, profit or loss before`
  line `income-tax, amount of income-tax paid, amount of income-tax accrued, stated capital, accumulated`
  line `earnings, number of employees and tangible assets not being cash or cash equivalents, with regard to`
  line `each country or territory in which the group operates;`
  line `( b ) the details of each constituent entity of the group including the country or territory in which`
  line `such constituent entity is incorporated or organised or established and the country or territory where it`
  line `is resident;`
  line `( c ) the nature and details of the main business activity or activities of each constituent entity; and`
  line `( d ) any other information as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 4 ) A constituent entity of an international group, resident in India, other than the entity referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ), shall furnish the report referred to in the said sub-section, in respect of the international`
  line `group for a reporting accounting year 3 [within the period as may be prescribed], if the parent entity is`
  line `resident of a country or territory, —`
  line `3 [( a ) where the parent entity is not obligated to file the report of the nature referred to in sub-`
  line `section ( 2 );]`
  line `4 [( aa )] with which India does not have an agreement providing for exchange of the report of the`
  line `nature referred to in sub-section ( 2 ); or`
  line `( b ) there has been a systemic failure of the country or territory and the said failure has been`
  line `intimated by the prescribed authority to such constituent entity:`
  line `Provided that where there are more than one such constituent entities of the group, resident in India,`
  line `the report shall be furnished by any one constituent entity, if, —`
  line `( a ) the international group has designated such entity to furnish the report in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) on behalf of all the constituent entities resident in India; and`
  line `( b ) the information has been conveyed in writing on behalf of the group to the prescribed`
  line authority.
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 113 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 55, for “on or before the due date specified under sub -section ( 1 ) of section 139, for furnishing`
  line `the return of income for the relevant accounting year” (w.r.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 55, ibid. (w.r.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `4. Clause ( a ) relettered as clause ( aa ) thereof by s. 55, ibid. (w.r.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_816_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_817:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-817
  sectionNo (817)
  orderNo 817
  title `Page 817`
  content obj_root_law_sections_817_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_817_footnotes
  sourcePage 817
obj_root_law_sections_817_content:
  string
  line 817
  line `( 5 ) Nothing contained in sub-section ( 4 ) shall apply, if, an alternate reporting entity of the`
  line `international group has furnished a report of the nature referred to in sub-section ( 2 ), with the tax`
  line `authority of the country or territory in which such entity is resident, on or before the date specified 1 [by`
  line `that country or territory] and the following conditions are satisfied, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the report is required to be furnished under the law for the time being in force in the said`
  line `country or territory;`
  line `( b ) the said country or territory has entered into an agreement with India providing for exchange`
  line `of the said report;`
  line `( c ) the prescribed authority has not conveyed any systemic failure in respect of the said country`
  line `or territory to any constituent entity of the group that is resident in India;`
  line `( d ) the said country or territory has been informed in writing by the constituent entity that it is the`
  line `alternate reporting entity on behalf of the international group; and`
  line `( e ) the prescribed authority has been informed by the 2 [entity] referred to in sub-section ( 4 ) in`
  line `accordance with sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 6 ) The prescribed authority may, for the purposes of determining the accuracy of the report furnished`
  line `by any reporting entity, by issue of a notice in writing, require the entity to produce such information and`
  line `document as may be specified in the notice within thirty days of the date of receipt of the notice:`
  line `Provided that the prescribed authority may, on an application made by such entity, extend the period`
  line `of thirty days by a further period not exceeding thirty days.`
  line `( 7 ) The provisions of this section shall not apply in respect of an international group for an`
  line `accounting year, if the total consolidated group revenue, as reflected in the consolidated financial`
  line `statement for the accounting year preceding such accounting year does not exceed the amount, as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line `( 8 ) The provisions of this section shall be applied in accordance with such guidelines and subject to`
  line `such conditions, as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 9 ) For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “accounting year” means,—`
  line `( i ) a previous year, in a case where the parent entity or alternate reporting entity is resident in`
  line `India; or`
  line `( ii ) an annual accounting period, with respect to which the parent entity of the international`
  line `group prepares its financial statements under any law for the time being in force or the applicable`
  line `accounting standards of the country or territory of which such entity is resident, in any other case;`
  line `3 [( b ) “agreement” means a combination of all of the following agreements, namely:––`
  line `( i ) an agreement entered into under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 90 or sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 90A; and`
  line `( ii ) an agreement for exchange of the report referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) and notified by the`
  line `Central Government;]`
  line `( c ) “alternate reporting entity” means any constituent entity of the international group that has`
  line `been designated by such group, in the place of the parent entity, to furnish the report of the nature`
  line `referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) in the country or territory in which the said constituent entity is resident`
  line `on behalf of such group;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 55, for “in the said sub - section” (w.r.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 55, ibid., for “entities” (w.r. e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 55, ibid., for clause ( b ) (w.r.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_817_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_818:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-818
  sectionNo (818)
  orderNo 818
  title `Page 818`
  content obj_root_law_sections_818_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_818_footnotes
  sourcePage 818
obj_root_law_sections_818_content:
  string
  line 818
  line `( d ) “ constituent entity ” means,—`
  line `( i ) any separate entity of an international group that is included in the consolidated financial`
  line `statement of the said group for financial reporting purposes, or may be so included for the said`
  line `purpose, if the equity share of any entity of the international group were to be listed on a stock`
  line exchange;
  line `( ii ) any such entity that is excluded from the consolidated financial statement of the`
  line `international group solely on the basis of size or materiality; or`
  line `( iii ) any permanent establishment of any separate business entity of the international group`
  line `included in 1 [sub-clause ( i ) or sub-clause ( ii )], if such business unit prepares a separate financial`
  line `statement for such permanent establishment for financial reporting, regulatory, tax reporting or`
  line `internal management control purposes;`
  line `( e ) “group” includes a parent entity and all the entities in respect of which, for the reason of`
  line `ownership or control, a consolidated financial statement for financial reporting purposes, —`
  line `( i ) is required to be prepared under any law for the time being in force or the accounting`
  line `standards of the country or territory of which the parent entity is resident; or`
  line `( ii ) would have been required to be prepared had the equity shares of any of the enterprises`
  line `were listed on a stock exchange in the country or territory of which the parent entity is resident;`
  line `( f ) “consolidated financial statement” means the financial statement of an international group in`
  line `which the assets, liabilities, income, expenses and cash flows of the parent entity and the constituent`
  line `entities are presented as those of a single economic entity;`
  line `( g ) “international group” means any group that includes,—`
  line `( i ) two or more enterprises which are resident of different countries or territories; or`
  line `( ii ) an enterprise, being a resident of one country or territory, which carries on any business`
  line `through a permanent establishment in other countries or territories;`
  line `( h ) “parent entity” means a constituent entity, of an international group holding, directly or`
  line `indirectly, an interest in one or more of the other constituent entities of the international group, such`
  line `that, —`
  line `( i ) it is required to prepare a consolidated financial statement under any law for the time`
  line `being in force or the accounting standards of the country or territory of which the entity is`
  line `resident; or`
  line `( ii ) it would have been required to prepare a consolidated financial statement had the equity`
  line `shares of any of the enterprises were listed on a stock exchange,`
  line `and, there is no other constituent entity of such group which, due to ownership of any interest, directly or`
  line `indirectly, in the first mentioned constituent entity, is required to prepare a consolidated financial`
  line `statement, under the circumstances referred to in 1 [sub-clause ( i ) or sub-clause ( ii )], that includes the`
  line `separate financial statement of the first mentioned constituent entity;`
  line `( i ) “permanent establishment” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( iiia ) of`
  line `section 92F;`
  line `( j ) “reporting accounting year” means the accounting year in re spect of which the financial and`
  line `operational results are required to be reflected in the report referred to in 2 [sub-section ( 2 ) and ( 4 )];`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 55, for “clause ( i ) or clause ( ii )” (w.r.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 55, ibid., for “sub -section ( 2 )” (w.r.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_818_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_819:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-819
  sectionNo (819)
  orderNo 819
  title `Page 819`
  content obj_root_law_sections_819_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_819_footnotes
  sourcePage 819
obj_root_law_sections_819_content:
  string
  line 819
  line `( k ) “reporting entity” means the constituent entity including the parent entity or the alternate`
  line `reporting entity, that is required to furnish a report of the nature referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 2 );`
  line `( l ) “systemic failure” with respect to a country or territory means that the co untry or territory has`
  line `an agreement with India providing for exchange of report of the nature referred to in sub-section ( 2 ),`
  line `but —`
  line `( i ) in violation of the said agreement, it has suspended automatic exchange; or`
  line `( ii ) has persistently failed to automatically provide to India the report in its possession in`
  line `respect of any international group having a constituent entity resident in India.]`
  line `1 [ 287. Publication of information respecting assessees in certain cases. — ( 1 ) If the Central`
  line `Government is of opinion that it is necessary or expedient in the public interest to publish the names of`
  line `any assessees and any other particulars relating to any proceedings 2 [or prosecutions] under this Act in`
  line `respect of such assessees, it may cause to be published such names and particulars in such manner as it`
  line `thinks fit.`
  line `3 [( 2 ) No publication under this section shall be made in relation to any penalty imposed under this Act`
  line `until the time for presenting an appeal to the 4 [*** Commissioner (Appeals)] has expired without an`
  line `appeal having been presented or the appeal, if presented, has been disposed of.]`
  line `Explanation. — In the case of a firm, company or other association of persons, the names of the`
  line `partners of the firm, directors, managing agents, secretaries and treasurers, or managers of the company,`
  line `or the members of the association, as the case may be, may also be published if, in the opinion of the`
  line `Central Government, the circumstances of the case justify it.]`
  line `5 [ 287A. Appearance by registered valuer in certain matters. — Any assessee who is entitled or`
  line `required to attend before any income-tax authority or the Appellate Tribunal in connection with any`
  line `matter relating to the valuation of any asset, otherwise than when required under section 131 to attend`
  line `personally for examination on oath or affirmation, may attend by a registered valuer.`
  line `Explanation. —In this section, “registered valuer” has the same meaning as in clause ( oaa ) of`
  line `section 2 of the Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957).`
  line `288. Appearance by authorised representative. — ( 1 ) Any assessee who is entitled or required to`
  line `attend before any income-tax authority or the Appellate Tribunal in connection with any proceeding`
  line `under this Act otherwise than when required under section 131 to attend personally for examination on`
  line `oath or affirmation, may, subject to the other provisions of this section, attend by an authorised`
  line representative.
  line `( 2 ) For the purposes of this section, “authorised representative” means a person authorised by the`
  line `assessee in writing to appear on his behalf, being —`
  line `( i ) a person related to the assessee in any manner, or a person regularly employed by the assessee;`
  line or
  line `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 1964, s. 45, for section 287 (w.e.f. 1-4-1964).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 77 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 77, ibid., for sub-section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `4. The words and brackets “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or the” omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `Which was substituted as “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)” for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” by Act 4 of 1988,`
  line `s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4- 1988) and the words and brackets “or the commissioner (Appeals)” were inserted after “Appellate`
  line `Assistant Commissioner” by Act 22 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 1 -4-1977).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 45 of 1972, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-1-1973).`
obj_root_law_sections_819_footnotes:
