  title `Page 820`
  content obj_root_law_sections_820_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_820_footnotes
  sourcePage 820
obj_root_law_sections_820_content:
  string
  line 820
  line `( ii ) any officer of a Scheduled Bank with which the assessee maintains a current account or has`
  line `other regular dealings; or`
  line `( iii ) any legal practitioner who is entitled to practise in any civil court in India; or`
  line `( iv ) an accountant; or`
  line `( v ) any person who has passed any accountancy examination recognised in this behalf by the`
  line `Board; or`
  line `( vi ) any person who has acquired such educational qualifications as the Board may prescribe for`
  line `this purpose; or`
  line `1 [( via ) any person who, before the coming into force of this Act in the Union territory of Dadra`
  line `and Nagar Haveli, Goa†, Daman and Diu, or Pondicherry, attended before an income -tax authority in`
  line `the said territory on behalf of any assessee otherwise than in the capacity of an employee or relative`
  line `of that assessee; or]`
  line `( vii ) any other person who, immediately before the commencement of this Act, was an`
  line `income-tax practitioner within the meaning of clause ( iv ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 61 of the Indian`
  line `Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922), and was actually practicing as such.`
  line `2 [ Explanation. —In this section, “accountant” means a chartered accountant as defined in clause ( b ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 2 of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949) who holds a valid`
  line `certificate of practice under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 6 of that Act, but does not include [except for the`
  line `purposes of representing the assessee under sub-section ( 1 )] —`
  line `( a ) in case of an assessee, being a company, the person who is not eligible for appointment as an`
  line `auditor of the said company in accordance with the provisions of sub-section ( 3 ) of section 141 of the`
  line `Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013); or`
  line `( b ) in any other case, —`
  line `( i ) the assessee himself or in case of the assessee, being a firm or association of persons or`
  line `Hindu undivided family, any partner of the firm, or member of the association or the family;`
  line `( ii ) in case of the assessee, being a trust or institution, any person referred to in clauses ( a ),`
  line `( b ), ( c ) and ( cc ) of sub-section ( 3 ) of section 13;`
  line `( iii ) in case of any person other than persons referred to in sub-clauses ( i ) and ( ii ), the person`
  line `who is competent to verify the return under section 139 in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of section 140;`
  line `( iv ) any relative of any of the persons referred to in sub-clauses ( i ), ( ii ) and ( iii );`
  line `( v ) an officer or employee of the assessee;`
  line `( vi ) an individual who is a partner, or who is in the employment, of an officer or employee of`
  line `the assessee;`
  line `1. Ins. by the Taxation Laws (Extension to Union Territories) Regulation, 1963 (3 of 1963), s. 3( 2 ) part II and the Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `† Goa has now become a State by Act 18 of 1987, s. 5 (w.e.f. 30 -5-1987).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 79, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_820_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_821:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-821
  sectionNo (821)
  orderNo 821
  title `Page 821`
  content obj_root_law_sections_821_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_821_footnotes
  sourcePage 821
obj_root_law_sections_821_content:
  string
  line 821
  line `( vii ) an individual who, or his relative or partner —`
  line `( I ) is holding any security of, or interest in, the assessee:`
  line `Provided that the relative may hold security or interest in the assessee of the face value`
  line `not exceeding one hundred thousand rupees;`
  line `( II ) is indebted to the assessee:`
  line `Provided that the relative may be indebted to the assessee for an amount not exceeding`
  line `one hundred thousand rupees;`
  line `( III ) has given a guarantee or provided any security in connection with the indebtedness`
  line `of any third person to the assessee:`
  line `Provided that the relative may give guarantee or provide any security in connection with`
  line `the indebtedness of any third person to the assessee for an amount not exceeding one hundred`
  line `thousand rupees;`
  line `( viii ) a person who, whether directly or indirectly, has business relationship with the assessee`
  line `of such nature as may be prescribed;`
  line `( ix ) a person who has been convicted by a court of an offence involving fraud and a period of`
  line `ten years has not elapsed from the date of such conviction.`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `( 4 ) No person —`
  line `( a ) who has been dismissed or removed from Government service after the 1st day of`
  line `April, 1938; or`
  line `( b ) who has been convicted of an offence connected with any income-tax proceeding or on whom`
  line `a penalty has been imposed under this Act, other than a penalty imposed on him under 2 [clause ( ii ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of] section 271 3 [clause ( d ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 272A or]; or`
  line `4 [( c ) who has become an insolvent; or`
  line `( d ) who has been convicted by a court for an offence involving fraud,`
  line `shall be qualified to represent an assessee under sub-section ( 1 ), for all times in the case of a person`
  line `referred to in clause ( a ), for such time as the Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Principal Commissioner or Commissioner may by order determine in the case of a person referred to in`
  line `clause ( b ), for the period during which the insolvency continues in the case of a person referred to in`
  line `clause ( c ), and for a period of ten years from the date of conviction in the case of a person referred to in`
  line `clause ( d ).]`
  line `( 5 ) If any person —`
  line `( a ) who is a legal practitioner or an accountant is found guilty of misconduct in his professional`
  line `capacity by any authority entitled to institute disciplinary proceedings against him, an order passed by`
  line `that authority shall have effect in relation to his right to attend before an income-tax authority as it has`
  line `in relation to his right to practise as a legal practitioner or accountant, as the case may be;`
  line `1. Sub-section ( 3 ) omitted by Act 67 of 1984, s. 52 (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 49 (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 114 (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 79, for certain words, brackets and letter (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_821_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_822:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-822
  sectionNo (822)
  orderNo 822
  title `Page 822`
  content obj_root_law_sections_822_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_822_footnotes
  sourcePage 822
obj_root_law_sections_822_content:
  string
  line 822
  line `( b ) who is not a legal practitioner or an accountant, is found guilty of misconduct in connection`
  line `with any income-tax proceedings by the prescribed authority, the prescribed authority may direct that`
  line `he shall thenceforth be disqualified to represent an assessee under sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 6 ) Any order or direction under clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 4 ) or clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 5 ) shall be`
  line `subject to the following conditions, namely: —`
  line `( a ) no such order or direction shall be made in respect of any person unless he has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard;`
  line `( b ) any person against whom any such order or direction is made may, within one month of the`
  line `making of the order or direction, appeal to the Board to have the order or direction cancelled; and`
  line `( c ) no such order or direction shall take effect until the expiration of one month from the making`
  line `thereof, or, where an appeal has been preferred, until the disposal of the appeal.`
  line `( 7 ) A person disqualified to represent an assessee by virtue of the provisions of sub-section ( 3 ) of`
  line `section 61 of the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922), shall be disqualified to represent an assessee`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `1 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, “relative” in relation to an individual, means—`
  line `( a ) spouse of the individual;`
  line `( b ) brother or sister of the individual;`
  line `( c ) brother or sister of the spouse of the individual;`
  line `( d ) any lineal ascendant or descendant of the individual;`
  line `( e ) any lineal ascendant or descendant of the spouse of the individual;`
  line `( f ) spouse of a person referred to in clause ( b ), clause ( c ), clause ( d ) or clause ( e );`
  line `( g ) any lineal descendant of a brother or sister of either the individual or the spouse of the`
  line individual.]
  line `2 [ 288A. Rounding off of income. — 3 [The amount of total income] computed in accordance with`
  line `the foregoing provisions of this Act shall be rounded off to the nearest multiple of ten rupees and for`
  line `this purpose any part of a rupee consisting of paise shall be ignored and thereafter if such amount is`
  line `not a multiple of ten, then, if the last figure in that amount is five or more, the amount shall be`
  line `increased to the next higher amount which is a multiple of ten and if the last figure is less than five,`
  line `the amount shall be reduced to the next lower amount which is a multiple of ten; and the amount so`
  line `rounded off shall be deemed to be the total income of the assessee for the purposes of this Act.]`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `5 [ 288B. Rounding off amount payable and refund due. — Any amount payable, and the amount`
  line `of refund due, under the provisions of this Act shall be rounded off to the nearest multiple of ten`
  line `rupees and for this purpose any part of a rupee consisting of paise shall be ignored and thereafter if`
  line `such amount is not a multiple of ten, then, if the last figure in that amount is five or more, the amount`
  line `shall be increased to the next higher amount which is a multiple of ten and if the last figure is less`
  line `than five, the amount shall be reduced to the next lower amount which is a multiple of ten.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 79 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 1966, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-4-1966).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 19 of 1968, s. 30 and the Third Schedule, for “( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ), the amount of`
  line `total income” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1969).`
  line `4. Sub-section ( 2 ) and Explanation, omitted by s. 30 and the Third Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1969).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 29 of 2006, s. 19, for section 288B (w.e.f. 13-7-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_822_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_823:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-823
  sectionNo (823)
  orderNo 823
  title `Page 823`
  content obj_root_law_sections_823_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_823_footnotes
  sourcePage 823
obj_root_law_sections_823_content:
  string
  line 823
  line `289. Receipt to be given. — A receipt shall be given for any money paid or recovered under this Act.`
  line `290. Indemnity. — Every person deducting, retaining, or paying any tax in pursuance of this Act in`
  line `respect of income belonging to another person is hereby indemnified for the deduction, retention, or`
  line `payment thereof.`
  line `291. Power to tender immunity from prosecution. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may, if it is of`
  line `opinion (the reasons for such opinion being recorded in writing) that with a view to obtaining the`
  line `evidence of any person appearing to have been directly or indirectly concerned in or privy to the`
  line `concealment of income or to the evasion of payment of tax on income 1 [it is necessary or expedient so to`
  line `do], tender to such person immunity from prosecution for any offence under this Act or under the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860), or under any other Central Act for the time being in force and also from the`
  line `imposition of any penalty under this Act on condition of his making a full and true disclosure of the`
  line `whole circumstances relating to the concealment of income or evasion of payment of tax on income.`
  line `( 2 ) A tender of immunity made to, and accepted by, the person concerned, shall, to the extent to`
  line `which the immunity extends, render him immune from prosecution for any offence in respect of which`
  line `the tender was made or from the imposition of any penalty under this Act.`
  line `( 3 ) If it appears to the Central Government that any person to whom immunity has been tendered`
  line `under this section has not complied with the condition on which the tender was made or is wilfully`
  line `concealing anything or is giving false evidence, the Central Government may record a finding to that`
  line `effect, and thereupon the immunity shall be deemed to have been withdrawn, and any such person may be`
  line `tried for the offence in respect of which the tender of immunity was made or for any other offence of`
  line `which he appears to have been guilty in connection with the same matter and shall also become liable to`
  line `the imposition of any penalty under this Act to which he would otherwise have been liable.`
  line `292. Cognizance of offences. — No court inferior to that of a presidency magistrate or a magistrate of`
  line `the first class shall try any offence under this Act.`
  line `2 [ 292A. Section 360 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973, and the Probation of Offenders`
  line `Act, 1958, not to apply. — Nothing contained in section 360 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974), or in the Probation of Offenders Act, 1958 (20 of 1958), shall apply to a person convicted of`
  line `an offence under this Act unless that person is under eighteen years of age.`
  line `292B. Return of income, etc., not to be invalid on certain grounds. — No return of income,`
  line `assessment, notice, summons or other proceeding, furnished or made or issued or taken or purported to`
  line `have been furnished or made or issued or taken in pursuance of any of the provisions of this Act shall be`
  line `invalid or shall be deemed to be invalid merely by reason of any mistake, defect or omission in such`
  line `return of income, assessment, notice, summons or other proceeding if such return of income, assessment,`
  line `notice, summons or other proceeding is in substance and effect in conformity with or according to the`
  line `intent and purpose of this Act.]`
  line `3 [ 292BB. Notice deemed to be valid in certain circumstances. — Where an assessee has appeared in`
  line `any proceeding or co-operated in any inquiry relating to an assessment or reassessment, it shall be`
  line `deemed that any notice under any provision of this Act, which is required to be served upon him, has been`
  line `duly served upon him in time in accordance with the provisions of this Act and such assessee shall be`
  line `precluded from taking any objection in any proceeding or inquiry under this Act that the notice was —`
  line `( a ) not served upon him; or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1963, s. 18 (w.e.f. 28-4-1963).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 78 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 56 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
