obj_root_law_sections_824_content:
  string
  line 824
  line `( b ) not served upon him in time; or`
  line `( c ) served upon him in an improper manner:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall apply where the assessee has raised such`
  line `objection before the completion of such assessment or reassessment.]`
  line `1 [ 292C. Presumption as to assets, books of account, etc. — 2 [( 1 )] Where any books of account, other`
  line `documents, money, bullion, jewellery or other valuable article or thing are or is found in the possession or`
  line `control of any person in the course of a search under section 132 3 [or survey under section 133A], it may,`
  line `in any proceeding under this Act, be presumed —`
  line `( i ) that such books of account, other documents, money, bullion, jewellery or other valuable`
  line `article or thing belong or belongs to such person;`
  line `( ii ) that the contents of such books of account and other documents are true; and`
  line `( iii ) that the signature and every other part of such books of account and other documents which`
  line `purport to be in the handwriting of any particular person or which may reasonably be assumed to`
  line `have been signed b y, or to be in the handwriting of, any particular person, are in that person’s`
  line `handwriting, and in the case of a document stamped, executed or attested, that it was duly stamped`
  line `and executed or attested by the person by whom it purports to have been so executed or attested.]`
  line `4 [( 2 ) Where any books of account, other documents or assets have been delivered to the requisitioning`
  line `officer in accordance with the provisions of section 132A, then, the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) shall`
  line `apply as if such books of account, other documents or assets which had been taken into custody from the`
  line `person referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ), as the case may be, of sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 132A, had been found in the possession or control of that person in the course of a search under`
  line `section 132.]`
  line `5 [ 292CC. Authorisation and assessment in case of search or requisition. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act, —`
  line `( i ) it shall not be necessary to issue an authorisation under section 132 or make a requisition`
  line `under section 132A separately in the name of each person;`
  line `( ii ) where an authorisation under section 132 has been issued or requisition under`
  line `section 132A has been made mentioning therein the name of more than one person, the mention of`
  line `such names of more than one person on such authorisation or requisition shall not be deemed to`
  line `construe that it was issued in the name of an association of persons or body of individuals consisting`
  line `of such persons.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding that an authorisation under section 132 has been issued or requisition`
  line `under section 132A has been made mentioning therein the name of more than one person, the assessment`
  line `or reassessment shall be made separately in the name of each of the persons mentioned in such`
  line `authorisation or requisition.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 78 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `2. Section 292C renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 18 of 2008, s. 57 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `3. Ins. by ibid. s. 57 (w.r.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `4. Ins. by ibid. s. 57 (w.r.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 112 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
