  content obj_root_law_sections_825_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_825_footnotes
  sourcePage 825
obj_root_law_sections_825_content:
  string
  line 825
  line `293. Bar of suits in civil courts. — No suit shall be brought in any civil court to set aside or modify`
  line `1 [any proceeding taken or order made] under this Act; and no prosecution, suit or other proceeding shall`
  line `lie against 2 [the Government or] any officer of the Government for anything in good faith done or`
  line `intended to be done under this Act.`
  line `3 [ 293A. Power to make exemption, etc., in relation to participation in the business of`
  line `prospecting for, extraction, etc., of mineral oils. — ( 1 ) If the Central Government is satisfied that it is`
  line `necessary or expedient so to do in the public interest, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make`
  line `an exemption, reduction in rate or other modification in respect of income-tax in favour of any class of`
  line `persons specified in sub-section ( 2 ) or in regard to the whole or any part of the income of such class of`
  line `persons 4 [or in regard to the status in which such class of persons or the members thereof are to be`
  line `assessed on their income from the business referred to in clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 2 ):`
  line `Provided that the notification for modification in respect of the status may be given effect from an`
  line `assessment year beginning on or after the 1st day of April, 1993.]`
  line `( 2 ) The persons referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) are the following, namely: —`
  line `( a ) persons with whom the Central Government has entered into agreements for the association`
  line `or participation of that Government or any person authorised by that Government in any business`
  line `consisting of the prospecting for or extraction or production of mineral oils;`
  line `( b ) persons providing any services or facilities or supplying any ship, aircraft, machinery or plant`
  line `(whether by way of sale or hire) in connection with any business consisting of the prospecting for or`
  line `extraction or production of mineral oils carried on by that Government or any person specified by that`
  line `Government in this behalf by notification in the Official Gazette; and`
  line `( c ) employees of the persons referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ).`
  line `( 3 ) Every notification issued under this section shall be laid before each House of Parliament.`
  line `5 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “mineral oil” includes petroleum and natural gas;`
  line `( b ) “status” means the category under which the assessee is assessed as “individual”, “Hindu`
  line `undivided family” and so on.]]`
  line `6 [ 293B. Power of Central Government or Board to condone delays in obtaining approval. —`
  line `Where, under any provision of this Act, the approval of the Central Government or the Board is required`
  line `to be obtained before a specified date, it shall be open to the Central Government or, as the case may be,`
  line `the Board to condone, for sufficient cause, any delay in obtaining such approval.]`
  line `7 [ 293C. Power to withdraw approval. — Where the Central Government or the Board or an income-`
  line `tax authority, who has been conferred upon the power under any provision of this Act to grant any`
  line `approval to any assessee, the Central Government or the Board or such authority may, notwithstanding`
  line `that a provision to withdraw such approval has not been specifically provided for in such provision,`
  line `withdraw such approval at any time:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 51, for “any order made” (w.r.e.f. 1 -3-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 5 of 1964, s. 46 (w.e.f. 1-4-1964).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 16 of 1981, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-4-1981).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 49 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 49, ibid., for the Explanation (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 121 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 79 (w.e.f. 1-10-2009).`
