  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_826_footnotes
  sourcePage 826
obj_root_law_sections_826_content:
  string
  line 826
  line `Provided that the Central Government or Board or income-tax authority shall, after giving a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the proposed withdrawal to the assessee concerned, at`
  line `any time, withdraw the approval after recording the reasons for doing so.]`
  line `294. Act to have effect pending legislative provision for charge of tax. — If on the 1st day of April`
  line `in any assessment year provision has not yet been made by a Central Act for the charging of income-tax`
  line `1 *** for that assessment year, this Act shall nevertheless have effect until such provision is so made as if`
  line `the provision in force in the preceding assessment year or the provision proposed in the Bill then before`
  line `Parliament, whichever is more favourable to the assessee, were actually in force.`
  line `2 [ 294A. Power to make exemption, etc., in relation to certain Union territories. — If the Central`
  line `Government considers it necessary or expedient so to do for avoiding any hardship or anomaly or`
  line `removing any difficulty that may arise as a result of the application of this Act to the Union territories of`
  line `Dadra and Nagar Haveli, Goa*, Daman and Diu, and Pondicherry, or in the case of the Union territory of`
  line `Pondicherry, for implementing any provision of the Treaty of Cession concluded between France and`
  line `India on the 28th day of May, 1956, that Government may, by general or special order, make an`
  line `exemption, reduction in rate or other modification in respect of income-tax or super-tax in favour of any`
  line `assessee or class of assessees or in regard to the whole or any part of the income of any assessee or class`
  line `of assessees:`
  line `Provided that the power conferred by this section shall not be exercisable after the 31st day of March,`
  line `1967, except for the purpose of rescinding an exemption, reduction or modification already made.]`
  line `295. Power to make rules. — ( 1 ) The Board may, subject to the control of the Central Government,`
  line `by notification in the Gazette of India, make rules for the whole or any part of India for carrying out the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters: —`
  line `( a ) the ascertainment and determination of any class of income;`
  line `( b ) the manner in which and the procedure by which the income shall be arrived at in the case`
  line `of —`
  line `( i ) income derived in part from agriculture and in part from business;`
  line `( ii ) persons residing outside India;`
  line `3 [( iii ) an individual who is liable to be assessed under the provisions of sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 64;]`
  line `( c ) the determination of the value of any perquisite chargeable to tax under this Act in such`
  line `manner and on such basis as appears to the Board to be proper and reasonable;`
  line `( d ) the percentage on the written down value which may be allowed as depreciation in respect of`
  line `buildings, machinery, plant or furniture;`
  line `4 [( dd ) the extent to which, and the conditions subject to which, any expenditure referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ) of section 37 may be allowed;]`
  line `5 [( dda ) the matters specified in sub-sections ( 2 ) and ( 3 ) of section 44AA;]`
  line `1. The words “or super - tax” omitted by Act 10 of 1965, s. 63 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
  line `2. Ins. by the Taxation Laws (Extension to Union Territories) Regulation, 1963 (3 of 1963), s. 3 and the Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 55 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 5 of 1964, s. 47 (w.e.f. 1-4-1964).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 79 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
