obj_root_law_sections_827_content:
  string
  line 827
  line `1 [ 2 [( e )] the conditions or limitations subject to which any payment of rent made by an assessee`
  line `shall be deducted under section 80GG;`
  line `3 [( ee ) the matters specified in Chapter X-A;]`
  line `( eea ) the cases, the nature and value of assets, the limits and heads of expenditure and the`
  line `outgoings, which are required to be prescribed under sub-section ( 6 ) of section 139;`
  line `( eeb ) the time within which any person may apply for the allotment of a permanent account`
  line `number, the form and the manner in which such application may be made and the particulars which`
  line `such application shall contain and the transactions with respect to which permanent account numbers`
  line `shall be quoted on documents relating to such transactions under section 139A;`
  line `4 [( eeba ) the documents, statements, receipts, certificates or audited reports which may not be`
  line `furnished along with the return but shall be produced before the Assessing Officer on demand`
  line `under section 139C;`
  line `( eebb ) the class or classes of persons who shall be required to furnish the return of income in`
  line `electronic form; the form and the manner of furnishing the said return in electronic form; documents,`
  line `statements, receipts, certificates or reports which shall not be furnished with the return in electronic`
  line `form and the computer resource or electronic record to which such return may be transmitted`
  line `under section 139D;]`
  line `( eec ) the form of the report of audit and the particulars which such report shall contain under sub-`
  line `section (2A) of section 142;]`
  line `3 [( eed ) remuneration of Chairperson and members of the Approving Panel under sub-section ( 18 )`
  line `and procedure and manner for constitution of, functioning and disposal of references by, the`
  line `Approving Panel under sub-section ( 21 ) of section 144BA;]`
  line `( f ) the manner in which and the period to which any such income as is referred to in section`
  line `180 may be allocated;`
  line `5 [( fa ) the form and manner in which the information relating to payment of any sum may be`
  line `furnished under sub-section ( 6 ) of section 195;]`
  line `( g ) the authority to be prescribed for any of the purposes of this Act;`
  line `( h ) the procedure for giving effect to the terms of any agreement for the granting of relief in`
  line `respect of double taxation or for the avoidance of double taxation which may be entered into by the`
  line `Central Government under this Act;`
  line `6 [( ha ) the procedure for granting of relief or deduction, as the case may be, of any income-tax`
  line `paid in any country or specified territory outside India, under section 90 or section 90A or section 91,`
  line `against the income-tax payable under this Act;]`
  line `( i ) the form and manner in which any application, claim, return or information may be made or`
  line `furnished and the fees that may be levied in respect of any application or claim;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 79 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `2. Clasue ( ee ) renumbered as clause ( e ) thereof by Act 17 of 2013, s. 59 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016). Earlier clause ( e ) omitted by`
  line `Act 18 of 2005, s. 64 (w.e.f. 1-4-2006) which was amended by Act 20 of 1967, s. 33 and the Third Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-`
  line `1968).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 59, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 79 (w.r.e.f. 1-6-2006).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 58 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 80 (w.e.f. 1-6-2015).`
