obj_root_law_sections_828_content:
  string
  line 828
  line `( j ) the manner in which any document required to be filed under this Act may be verified;`
  line `( k ) the procedure to be followed on applications for refunds;`
  line `1 [( kk ) the procedure to be followed in calculating interest payable by assessees or interest payable`
  line `by Government to assessees under any provision of this Act, including the rounding off of the period`
  line `for which such interest is to be calculated in cases where such period includes a fraction of a month,`
  line `and specifying the circumstances in which and the extent to which petty amounts of interest payable`
  line `by assessees may be ignored;]`
  line `( l ) the regulation of any matter for which provision is made in section 230;`
  line `( m ) the form and manner in which any appeal or cross-objection may be filed under this Act, the`
  line `fee payable in respect thereof and the manner in which intimation of any such order as is referred to`
  line `in clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 249 may be served;`
  line `2 [( mm ) the circumstances in which, the conditions subject to which and the manner in which, the`
  line `3 [*** or the Commissioner (Appeals)] may permit an appellant to produce evidence which he did not`
  line `produce or which he was not allowed to produce before the 4 [Assessing Officer];]`
  line `5 [( mma ) the form in which the statement under section 285B shall be delivered to the 4 [Assessing`
  line Officer];]
  line `( n ) the maintenance of a register of persons other than legal practitioners or accountants as`
  line `defined in sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288 practising before income-tax authorities and for the`
  line `constitution of and the procedure to be followed by the authority referred to in sub-section ( 5 ) of that`
  line section;
  line `( o ) the issue of certificate verifying the payment of tax by assessees;`
  line `( p ) any other matter which by this Act is to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line `( 3 ) In cases coming under clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 2 ), where the income liable to tax cannot be`
  line `definitely ascertained, or can be ascertained only with an amount of trouble and expense to the assessee`
  line `which in the opinion of the Board is unreasonable, the rules made under this section may —`
  line `( a ) prescribe methods by which an estimate of such income may be made; and`
  line `( b ) in cases coming under sub-clause ( i ) of clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 2 ) specify the proportion of`
  line `the income which shall be deemed to be income liable to tax,`
  line `and an assessment based on such estimate or proportion shall be deemed to be duly made in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of this Act.`
  line `6 [( 4 ) The power to make rules conferred by this section shall include the power to give retrospective`
  line `effect, from a date not earlier than the date of commencement of this Act, to the rules or any of them and,`
  line `unless the contrary is permitted (whether expressly or by necessary implication), no retrospective effect`
  line `shall be given to any rule so as to prejudicially affect the interests of assessees.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 55 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `3. The words “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or the” omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998). Earlier the`
  line `words “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)” were substituted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Appellate A ssistant`
  line `Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4- 1988) and the words “or the Commissioner (Appeals)” were inserted by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39`
  line `and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 79 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 26 of 1974, s. 14 (w.e.f. 18-8-1974).`
