  content obj_root_law_sections_829_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_829_footnotes
  sourcePage 829
obj_root_law_sections_829_content:
  string
  line 829
  line `1 [ 2 [ 296. Rules and certain notifications to be placed before Parliament. — The Central`
  line `Government shall cause every rule made under this Act, 3 [the rules of procedure framed by the`
  line `Settlement Commission under sub-section ( 7 ) of section 245F, the Authority for Advance Rulings`
  line `under section 245V and the Appellate Tribunal under sub-section ( 5 ) of section 255] and 4 [every`
  line `notification issued before the 1st day of June, 2007 under sub-clause ( iv ) of clause ( 23C ) of`
  line `section 10] 5 [and every notification issued under sub-section ( 1C ) of section 139] 6 [or third proviso to`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 153A or second proviso to sub-section ( 1 ) of section 153C] to be laid as soon as`
  line `may be after the rule is made or the notification is issued before each House of Parliament while it is in`
  line `session, for a total period of thirty days, which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or notification or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule or notification should not be made or issued, that rule or notification shall`
  line `thereafter have effect, only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule or notification.]]`
  line `297. Repeals and savings. — ( 1 ) The Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922), is hereby repealed.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding the repeal of the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922) (hereinafter referred`
  line `to as the repealed Act), —`
  line `( a ) where a return of income has been filed before the commencement of this Act by any person`
  line `for any assessment year, proceedings for the assessment of that person for that year may be taken and`
  line `continued as if this Act had not been passed;`
  line `( b ) where a return of income is filed after the commencement of this Act otherwise than in`
  line `pursuance of a notice under section 34 of the repealed Act by any person for the assessment year`
  line `ending on the 31st day of March, 1962, or any earlier year, the assessment of that person for that year`
  line `shall be made in accordance with the procedure specified in this Act;`
  line `( c ) any proceeding pending on the commencement of this Act before any income-tax authority,`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal or any court, by way of appeal, reference, or revision, shall be continued and`
  line `disposed of as if this Act had not been passed;`
  line `( d ) where in respect of any assessment year after the year ending on the 31st day of`
  line `March, 1940, —`
  line `( i ) a notice under section 34 of the repealed Act had been issued before the commencement of`
  line `this Act, the proceedings in pursuance of such notice may be continued and disposed of as if this`
  line `Act had not been passed;`
  line `( ii ) any income chargeable to tax had escaped assessment within the meaning of that`
  line `expression in section 147 and no proceedings under section 34 of the repealed Act in respect of`
  line `any such income are pending at the commencement of this Act, a notice under section 148 may,`
  line `subject to the provisions contained in section 149 or section 150, be issued with respect to that`
  line `assessment year and all the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly;`
  line `( e ) 7 [subject to the provisions of clause ( g ) and clause ( j ) of this sub-section,] section 23A of the`
  line `repealed Act shall continue to have effect in relation to the assessment of any company or its`
  line `shareholders for the assessment year ending on the 31st day of March, 1962 or any earlier year, and`
  line `the provisions of the repealed Act shall apply to all matters arising out of such assessment as fully and`
  line `effectually as if this Act had not been passed;`
  line `1. Restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f.1-4-1989). Earlier it was substituted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 122 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 80, f or “section 296” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1976).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 49 (w.e.f. 1-6-1994).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 80, for “every notification issued under sub -clause ( iv ) of clause ( 23C ) of section 10”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-6-2011).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 113 (w.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 13 of 1963, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
obj_root_law_sections_829_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_830:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-830
  sectionNo (830)
  orderNo 830
  title `Page 830`
  content obj_root_law_sections_830_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_830_footnotes
  sourcePage 830
obj_root_law_sections_830_content:
  string
  line 830
  line `( f ) any proceeding for the imposition of a penalty in respect of any assessment completed before`
  line `the first day of April, 1962, may be initiated and any such penalty may be imposed as if this Act had`
  line `not been passed;`
  line `( g ) any proceeding for the imposition of a penalty in respect of any assessment for the year`
  line `ending on the 31st day of March, 1962, or any earlier year, which is completed on or after the 1st day`
  line `of April, 1962, may be initiated and any such penalty may be imposed under this Act;`
  line `( h ) any election or declaration made or option exercised by an assessee under any provision of the`
  line `repealed Act and in force immediately before the commencement of this Act shall be deemed to have`
  line `been an election or declaration made or option exercised under the corresponding provision of this`
  line Act;
  line `( i ) where, in respect of any assessment completed before the commencement of this Act, a refund`
  line `falls due after such commencement or default is made after such commencement in the payment of`
  line `any sum due under such completed assessment, the provisions of this Act relating to interest payable`
  line `by the Central Government on refunds and interest payable by the assessee for default shall apply;`
  line `( j ) any sum payable by way of income-tax, super-tax, interest, penalty or otherwise under the`
  line `repealed Act may be recovered under this Act, but without prejudice to any action already taken for`
  line `the recovery of such sum under the repealed Act;`
  line `( k ) any agreement entered into, appointment made, approval given, recognition granted, direction,`
  line `instruction, notification, order or rule issued under any provision of the repealed Act shall, so far as it`
  line `is not inconsistent with the corresponding provision of this Act, be deemed to have been entered into,`
  line `made, granted, given or issued under the corresponding provision aforesaid and shall continue in`
  line `force accordingly;`
  line `( l ) any notification issued under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 60 1 [ or section 60A] of the repealed`
  line `Act and in force immediately before the commencement of this Act shall, to the extent to which`
  line `provision has not been made under this Act, continue in force 2 ***:`
  line `3 [Provided that the Central Government may rescind any such notification or amend it so as to`
  line `rescind any exemption, reduction in rate or other modification made thereunder;]`
  line `( m ) where the period prescribed for any application, appeal, reference or revision under the`
  line `repealed Act had expired on or before the commencement of this Act, nothing in this Act shall be`
  line `construed as enabling any such application, appeal, reference or revision to be made under this Act by`
  line `reason only of the fact that a longer period therefor is prescribed or provision is made for extension of`
  line `time in suitable cases by the appropriate authority.`
  line `298. Power to remove difficulties. — ( 1 ) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act the Central Government may, by general or special order, do anything not inconsistent with such`
  line `provisions which appears to it to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty.`
  line `( 2 ) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, any such order may`
  line `provide for the adaptations or modifications subject to which the repealed Act shall apply in relation to`
  line `the assessments for the assessment year ending on the 31st day of March, 1962, or any earlier year.`
  line `4 [( 3 ) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this Act as amended by the Direct Tax`
  line `Laws (Amendment) Act, 1987, the Central Government may, by order, do anything not inconsistent with`
  line `such provisions for the purpose of removing the difficulty:`
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiration of three years from the 1st day of April,`
  line 1988.
  line `( 4 ) Every order made under sub-section ( 3 ) shall be laid before each House of Parliament.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1966, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-1962).`
  line `2. The words “until rescinded by the Central Government” omitt ed by Act 54 of 1972, s. 7 (w.e.f. 9-9-1972).`
  line `3. The proviso added by s. 7, ibid., (w.e.f. 9-9-1972).`
  line `4. Sub-section ( 3 ) added by Act 4 of 1988, s. 123 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_830_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_831:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-831
  sectionNo (831)
  orderNo 831
  title `Page 831`
  content obj_root_law_sections_831_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_831_footnotes
  sourcePage 831
obj_root_law_sections_831_content:
  string
  line 831
  line `THE FIRST SCHEDULE`
  line `I NSURANCE BUSINESS`
  line `[ See section 44]`
  line `A. — Life insurance business`
  line `1. Profits of life insurance business to be compu ted separately. — In the case of a person who`
  line `carries on or at any time in the previous year carried on life insurance business, the profits and gains of`
  line `such person from that business shall be computed separately from his profits and gains from any other`
  line business.
  line `1 [ 2. Computation of profits of life insurance business. — The profits and gains of life insurance`
  line `business shall be taken to be the annual average of the surplus arrived at by adjusting the surplus or deficit`
  line `disclosed by the actuarial valuation made in accordance with the Insurance Act, 1938 (4 of 1938), in`
  line `respect of the last inter-valuation period ending before the commencement of the assessment year, so as to`
  line `exclude from it any surplus or deficit included therein which was made in any earlier inter-valuation`
  line period.]
  line `3. [ Deductions.] Omitted by the Finance Act, 1976 (66 of 1976), s. 23 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1977). Earlier, the`
  line `rule was first amended by the Finance Act, 1966 (13 of 1966), s. 36 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1966) and by the Finance`
  line `Act, 1965 (10 of 1965), s. 65 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1965).]`
  line `4. Adjustment of tax paid by deduction at source. — Where for any year an assessment of the`
  line `profits of life insurance business is made in accordance with the annual average of a surplus disclosed by`
  line `a valuation for an inter-valuation period exceeding twelve months, then, in computing the income-tax`
  line `payable for that year, credit shall not be given in accordance with section 199 for the income-tax paid in`
  line `the previous year, but credit shall be given for the annual average of the income-tax paid by deduction at`
  line `source from interest on securities or otherwise during such period.`
  line `B. — Other insurance business`
  line `5. Computation of profits and gains of other insurance business. — The profits and gains of any`
  line `business of insurance other than life insurance shall be taken to be the 2 [profit before tax and`
  line `appropriations as disclosed in the profit and loss account prepared in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `the Insurance Act, 1938 (4 of 1938) or the rules made thereunder or the provisions of the Insurance`
  line `Regulatory and Development Authority Act, 1999 (4 of 1999) or the regulations made thereunder,]`
  line `subject to the following adjustments: —`
  line `( a ) subject to the other provisions of this rule, 3 [any expenditure or allowance including any`
  line `amount debited to the profit and loss account either by way of a provision for any tax, dividend,`
  line `reserve or any other provision as may be prescribed] which is not admissible under the provisions`
  line `of 4 [sections 30 to 43B] in computing the profits and gains of a business shall be added back;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 66 of 1976, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-1977).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 80, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-2011).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 64, for “any expenditure or allowance” (w.r.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 126, for “section 30 to 43A” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_831_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_832:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-832
  sectionNo (832)
  orderNo 832
  title `Page 832`
  content obj_root_law_sections_832_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_832_footnotes
  sourcePage 832
obj_root_law_sections_832_content:
  string
  line 832
  line `1 [( b ) ( i ) any gain or loss on realisation of investments shall be added or deducted, as the case may`
  line `be, if such gain or loss is not credited or debited to the profit and loss account;`
  line `( ii ) any provision for diminution in the value of investment debited to the profit and loss account,`
  line `shall be added back;]`
  line `( c ) such amount carried over to a reserve for unexpired risks as may be prescribed in this behalf`
  line `shall be allowed as a deduction.`
  line `C. — Other provisions`
  line `6. Profits and gains of non-resident person. — ( 1 ) The profits and gains of the branches in India of a`
  line `person not resident in India and carrying on any business of insurance, may, in the absence of more`
  line `reliable data, be deemed to be that proportion of the world income of such person which corresponds to`
  line `the proportion which his premium income derived from India bears to his total premium income.`
  line `( 2 ) For the purposes of this rule, the world income in relation to life insurance business of a person`
  line `not resident in India shall be computed in the manner laid down in this Act for the computation of the`
  line `profits and gains of life insurance business carried on in India.`
  line `7. Interpretation. — ( 1 ) For the purposes of these rules —`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `( ii ) “ investments ” includes securities, stocks and shares;`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `( iv ) “life insurance business” means life insurance business as defined in clause ( 11 ) of section 2`
  line `of the Insurance Act, 1938 (4 of 1938);`
  line `( v ) “rule” means a rule contained in this Schedule.`
  line `( 2 ) References in these rules to the Insurance Act, 1938 (4 of 1938), or any provision thereof, shall, in`
  line `relation to the Life Insurance Corporation of India, be construed as references to that Act or provision as`
  line `read with section 43 of the Life Insurance Corporation Act, 1956 (31 of 1956).`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 52, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2011).`
  line `2. Clause ( i ) omitted by Act 66 of 1976, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-1977). Earlier clause ( i ) was amended by Act 20 of 1967, s. 32`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1967).`
  line `3. Clause ( iii ) omitted by s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1977).`
obj_root_law_sections_832_footnotes:
