  line
obj_root_law_sections_847:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-847
  sectionNo (847)
  orderNo 847
  title `Page 847`
  content obj_root_law_sections_847_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_847_footnotes
  sourcePage 847
obj_root_law_sections_847_content:
  string
  line 847
  line `PART IV`
  line `A PPOINTMENT OF RECEIVER`
  line `69. Appointment of receiver for business. — ( 1 ) Where the property of a defaulter consists of a`
  line `business, the Tax Recovery Officer may attach the business and appoint a person as receiver to manage`
  line `the business.`
  line `( 2 ) Attachment of a business under this rule shall be made by an order prohibiting the defaulter from`
  line `transferring or charging the business in any way and prohibiting all persons from taking any benefit under`
  line `such transfer or charge, and intimating that the business has been attached under this rule. A copy of the`
  line `order of attachment shall be served on the defaulter, and another copy shall be affixed on a conspicuous`
  line `part of the premises in which the business is carried on and on the notice board of the office of the Tax`
  line `Recovery Officer.`
  line `70. Appointment of receiver for immovable property. — Where immovable property is attached, the`
  line `Tax Recovery Officer may, instead of directing a sale of the property, appoint a person as receiver to`
  line `manage such property.`
  line `71. Powers of receiver. — ( 1 ) Where any business or other property is attached and taken under`
  line `management under the foregoing rules, the receiver shall, subject to the control of the Tax Recovery`
  line `Officer, have such powers as may be necessary for the proper management of the property and the`
  line `realisation of the profits, or rents and profits, thereof.`
  line `( 2 ) The profits, or rents and profits, of such business or other property, shall, after defraying the`
  line `expenses of management, be adjusted towards discharge of the arrears, and the balance, if any, shall be`
  line `paid to the defaulter.`
  line `72. Withdrawal of management. — The attachment and management under the foregoing rules may`
  line `be withdrawn at any time at the discretion of the Tax Recovery Officer, or if the arrears are discharged by`
  line `receipt of such profits and rents or are otherwise paid.`
  line `PART V`
  line `A RREST AND DETENTION OF THE DEFAULTER`
  line `73. Notice to show cause. — ( 1 ) No order for the arrest and detention in civil prison of a defaulter`
  line `shall be made unless the Tax Recovery Officer has issued and served a notice upon the defaulter calling`
  line `upon him to appear before him on the date specified in the notice and to show cause why he should not be`
  line `committed to the civil prison, and unless the Tax Recovery Officer, for reasons recorded in writing, is`
  line `satisfied —`
  line `( a ) that the defaulter, with the object or effect of obstructing the execution of the certificate, has,`
  line `after 1 [the drawing up of the certificate by the Tax Recovery Officer], dishonestly transferred,`
  line `concealed, or removed any part of his property, or`
  line `( b ) that the defaulter has, or has had since 1 [the drawing up of the certificate by the Tax Recovery`
  line `Officer], the means to pay the arrears or some substantial part thereof and refuses or neglects or has`
  line `refused or neglected to pay the same.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-rule ( 1 ), a warrant for the arrest of the defaulter may`
  line `be issued by the Tax Recovery Officer if the Tax Recovery Officer is satisfied, by affidavit or otherwise,`
  line `that with the object or effect of delaying the execution of the certificate, the defaulter is likely to abscond`
  line `or leave the local limits of the jurisdiction of the Tax Recovery Officer.`
  line `( 3 ) Where appearance is not made in obedience to a notice issued and served under sub-rule ( 1 ), the`
  line `Tax Recovery Officer may issue a warrant for the arrest of the defaulter.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 124, for, “the receipt of the certificate in the office of the Tax Recovery Office” (w.e.f. 1 -4-`
  line `1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_847_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_848:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-848
  sectionNo (848)
  orderNo 848
  title `Page 848`
  content obj_root_law_sections_848_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_848_footnotes
  sourcePage 848
obj_root_law_sections_848_content:
  string
  line 848
  line `1 [( 3A ) A warrant of arrest issued by a Tax Recovery Officer under sub-rule ( 2 ) or sub-rule ( 3 ) may`
  line `also be executed by any other Tax Recovery Officer within whose jurisdiction the defaulter may for the`
  line `time being be found.]`
  line `( 4 ) Every person arrested in pursuance of a warrant of arrest under 2 [this rule] shall be brought before`
  line `the Tax Recovery Officer 3 [issuing the warrant] as soon as practicable and in any event within twenty-`
  line `four hours of his arrest (exclusive of the time required for the journey):`
  line `Provided that, if the defaulter pays the amount entered in the warrant of arrest as due and the costs of`
  line `the arrest to the officer arresting him, such officer shall at once release him.`
  line `1 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this rule, where the defaulter is a Hindu undivided family, the`
  line `karta thereof shall be deemed to be the defaulter.]`
  line `74. Hearing. — When a defaulter appears before the Tax Recovery Officer in obedience to a notice to`
  line `show cause or is brought before the Tax Recovery Officer under rule 73, 4 [the Tax Recovery Officer shall`
  line `proceed to hear the 5 [Assessing Officer] and take all such evidence as may be produced by him in support`
  line `of execution by arrest, and then give the defaulter] an opportunity of showing cause why he should not be`
  line `committed to the civil prison.`
  line `75. Custody pending hearing. — Pending the conclusion of the inquiry, the Tax Recovery Officer`
  line `may, in his discretion, order the defaulter to be detained in the custody of such officer as the Tax`
  line `Recovery Officer may think fit or release him on his furnishing security to the satisfaction of the Tax`
  line `Recovery Officer for his appearance when required.`
  line `76. Order of detention. — ( 1 ) Upon the conclusion of the inquiry, the Tax Recovery Officer may`
  line `make an order for the detention of the defaulter in the civil prison and shall in that event cause him to be`
  line `arrested if he is not already under arrest:`
  line `Provided that in order to give the defaulter an opportunity of satisfying the arrears, the Tax Recovery`
  line `Officer may, before making the order of detention, leave the defaulter in the custody of the officer`
  line `arresting him or of any other officer for a specified period not exceeding 15 days, or release him on his`
  line `furnishing security to the satisfaction of the Tax Recovery Officer for his appearance at the expiration of`
  line `the specified period if the arrears are not so satisfied.`
  line `( 2 ) When the Tax Recovery Officer does not make an order of detention under sub-rule ( 1 ) he shall, if`
  line `the defaulter is under arrest, direct his release.`
  line `77. Detention in and release from prison. — ( 1 ) Every person detained in the civil prison in`
  line `execution of a certificate may be so detained, —`
  line `( a ) where the certificate is for a demand of an amount exceeding two hundred and fifty rupees —`
  line `for a period of six months, and`
  line `( b ) in any other case — for a period of six weeks:`
  line `Provided that he shall be released from such detention —`
  line `( i ) on the amount mentioned in the warrant for his detention being paid to the officer-in-charge of`
  line `the civil prison, or`
  line `6 [( ii ) on the request of the Tax Recovery Officer on any ground other than the grounds mentioned`
  line `in rules 78 and 79.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 81 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 81, ibid., for “sub -rule ( 1 ) or sub-rule ( 2 )” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1975).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 81, ibid., for “Tax Recovery Officer” (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `4. Restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 54, ibid., for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 124, for clause ( ii ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier amended by Act 3 of 1989, s. 55 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_848_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_849:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-849
  sectionNo (849)
  orderNo 849
  title `Page 849`
  content obj_root_law_sections_849_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_849_footnotes
  sourcePage 849
obj_root_law_sections_849_content:
  string
  line 849
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `( 2 ) A defaulter released from detention under this rule shall not, merely by reason of his release, be`
  line `discharged from his liability for the arrears; but he shall not be liable to be rearrested under the certificate`
  line `in execution of which he was detained in the civil prison.`
  line `78. Release. — ( 1 ) The Tax Recovery Officer may order the release of a defaulter who has been`
  line `arrested in execution of a certificate upon being satisfied that he has disclosed the whole of his property`
  line `and has placed it at the disposal of the Tax Recovery Officer and that he has not committed any act of bad`
  line faith.
  line `( 2 ) If the Tax Recovery Officer has ground for believing the disclosure made by a defaulter under`
  line `sub-rule ( 1 ) to have been untrue, he may order the rearrest of the defaulter in execution of the certificate,`
  line `but the period of his detention in the civil prison shall not in the aggregate exceed that authorised by`
  line `rule 77.`
  line `79. Release on ground of illness. — ( 1 ) At any time after a warrant for the arrest of a defaulter has`
  line `been issued, the Tax Recovery Officer may cancel it on the ground of his serious illness.`
  line `( 2 ) Where a defaulter has been arrested, the Tax Recovery Officer may release him if, in the opinion`
  line `of the Tax Recovery Officer, he is not in a fit state of health to be detained in the civil prison.`
  line `( 3 ) Where a defaulter has been committed to the civil prison, he may be released therefrom by the`
  line `Tax Recovery Officer on the ground of the existence of any infectious or contagious disease, or on the`
  line `ground of his suffering from any serious illness.`
  line `( 4 ) A defaulter released under this rule may be rearrested, but the period of his detention in the civil`
  line `prison shall not in the aggregate exceed that authorised by rule 77.`
  line `80. Entry into dwelling house. — For the purpose of making an arrest under this Schedule —`
  line `( a ) no dwelling house shall be entered after sunset and before sunrise;`
  line `( b ) no outer door of a dwelling house shall be broken open unless such dwelling house or a`
  line `portion thereof is in the occupancy of the defaulter and he or other occupant of the house refuses or in`
  line `any way prevents access thereto; but, when the person executing any such warrant has duly gained`
  line `access to any dwelling house, he may break open the door of any room or apartment if he has reason`
  line `to believe that the defaulter is likely to be found there;`
  line `( c ) no room, which is in the actual occupancy of a woman who, according to the customs of the`
  line `country, does not appear in public, shall be entered into unless the officer authorised to make the`
  line `arrest has given notice to her that she is at liberty to withdraw and has given her reasonable time and`
  line `facility for withdrawing.`
  line `81. Prohibition against arrest of women or minors, etc. — The Tax Recovery Officer shall not`
  line `order the arrest and detention in the civil prison of —`
  line `( a ) a woman, or`
  line `( b ) any person who, in his opinion, is a minor or of unsound mind.`
  line `1. The proviso omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 124 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_849_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_850:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-850
  sectionNo (850)
  orderNo 850
  title `Page 850`
  content obj_root_law_sections_850_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_850_footnotes
  sourcePage 850
obj_root_law_sections_850_content:
  string
  line 850
  line `PART VI`
  line `M ISCELLANEOUS`
  line `82. Officers deemed to be acting judicially. — Every 1 [ 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner] or 3 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner], Tax Recovery Officer] or other officer`
  line `acting under this Schedule shall, in the discharge of his functions under this Schedule, be deemed to be`
  line `acting judicially within the meaning of the Judicial Officers Protection Act, 1850 (18 of 1850).`
  line `83. Power to take evidence. — Every 1 [ 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or`
  line `3 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner], Tax Recovery Officer] or other officer acting under the`
  line `provisions of this Schedule shall have the powers of a civil court while trying a suit for the purpose of`
  line `receiving evidence, administering oaths, enforcing the attendance of witnesses and compelling the`
  line `production of documents.`
  line `84. Continuance of certificate. — No certificate shall cease to be in force by reason of the death of`
  line `the defaulter.`
  line `85. Procedure on death of defaulter. — 4 [If at any time after the issue of the certificate by the`
  line `Assessing Officer to the Tax Recovery Officer] the defaulter dies, the proceedings under this Schedule`
  line `(except arrest and detention) may be continued against the legal representative of the defaulter, and the`
  line `provisions of this Schedule shall apply as if the legal representative were the defaulter.`
  line `86. Appeals. — 5 [( 1 ) An appeal from any original order passed by the Tax Recovery Officer under this`
  line `Schedule, not being an order which is conclusive, shall lie to the 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner] or 3 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner].]`
  line `( 2 ) Every appeal under this rule must be presented within thirty days from the date of the order`
  line `appealed against.`
  line `( 3 ) Pending the decision of any appeal, execution of the certificate may be stayed if the appellate`
  line `authority so directs, but not otherwise.`
  line `6 [( 4 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-rule ( 1 ), where a 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Chief Commissioner] or 3 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner] is authorised to exercise powers as`
  line `such in respect of any area, then, all appeals against the orders passed before the date of such`
  line `authorisation by any Tax Recovery Officer authorised to exercise powers as such in respect of that area,`
  line `or an area which is included in that area, shall lie to such 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner] or 3 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner].]`
  line `87. Review. — Any order passed under this Schedule may, after notice to all persons interested, be`
  line `reviewed by the 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 3 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner], Tax Recovery Officer or other officer who made the order, or by his successor in office,`
  line `on account of any mistake apparent from the record.`
  line `88. Recovery from surety. — Where any person has under this Schedule become surety for the`
  line `amount due by the defaulter, he may be proceeded against under this Schedule as if he were the defaulter.`
  line `89. [Penalties. ] — Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988), s. 126`
  line `( w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 124, for “Tax Recovery Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989). Earlier substituted by`
  line `Act 32 of 1971, s. 29, for “Tax Recovery Office” (w.e.f. 1-1-1972).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. Restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 124, for sub-rule ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 124, ibid., for sub-rule ( 4 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_850_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_851:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-851
  sectionNo (851)
  orderNo 851
  title `Page 851`
  content obj_root_law_sections_851_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_851_footnotes
  sourcePage 851
obj_root_law_sections_851_content:
  string
  line 851
  line `90. Subsistence allowance. — ( 1 ) When a defaulter is arrested or detained in the civil prison, the sum`
  line `payable for the subsistence of the defaulter from the time of arrest until he is released shall be borne by`
  line `the 1 [Assessing Officer].`
  line `( 2 ) Such sum shall be calculated on the scale fixed by the State Government for the subsistence of`
  line `judgment-debtors arrested in execution of a decree of a civil court.`
  line `( 3 ) Sums payable under this rule shall be deemed to be costs in the proceeding:`
  line `Provided that the defaulter shall not be detained in the civil prison or arrested on account of any sum`
  line `so payable.`
  line `91. Forms. — The Board may prescribe the form to be used for any order, notice, warrant, or`
  line `certificate to be issued under this Schedule.`
  line `92.Power to make rules. — ( 1 ) The Board may make rules, consistent with the provisions of this Act,`
  line `regulating the procedure to be followed by 2 [Principal Chief Commissioners or Chief Commissioners],`
  line `3 [Principal Commissioners or Commissioners], Tax Recovery Officers and other officers acting under this`
  line Schedule.
  line `( 2 ) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the power conferred by sub-rule (1), such`
  line `rules may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the area within which 2 [Principal Chief Commissioners or Chief Commissioners], 3 [Principal`
  line `Commissioners or Commissioners] or Tax Recovery Officers may exercise jurisdiction;`
  line `( b ) the manner in which any property sold under this Schedule may be delivered;`
  line `( c ) the execution of a document or the endorsement of a negotiable instrument or a share in a`
  line `corporation, by or on behalf of the Tax Recovery Officer, where such execution or endorsement is`
  line `required to transfer such negotiable instrument or share to a person who has purchased it under a sale`
  line `under this Schedule;`
  line `( d ) the procedure for dealing with resistance or obstruction offered by any person to a purchaser`
  line `of any immovable property sold under this Schedule, in obtaining possession of the property;`
  line `( e ) the fees to be charged for any process issued under this Schedule;`
  line `( f ) the scale of charges to be recovered in respect of any other proceeding taken under this`
  line Schedule;
  line `( g ) recovery of poundage fee;`
  line `( h ) the maintenance and custody, while under attachment, of livestock or other movable`
  line `property, the fees to be charged for such maintenance and custody, the sale of such livestock or`
  line `property, and the disposal of proceeds of such sale;`
  line `( i ) the mode of attachment of business.`
  line `93. Saving regarding charge. — Nothing in this Schedule shall affect any provision of this Act`
  line `whereunder the tax is a first charge upon any asset.`
  line `4 [ 94. Continuance of certain pending proceedings and power to remove difficulties. — All`
  line `proceedings for the recovery of tax pending immediately before the coming into force of the amendments`
  line `to this Schedule by the Direct Tax Laws (Amendment) Act, 1987 shall be continued under this Schedule`
  line `as amended by that Act from the stage they had reached, and, for this purpose, every certificate issued by`
  line `the 5 [Assessing Officer] under section 222 before such amendment shall be deemed to be a certificate`
  line `drawn up by the Tax Recovery Officer under that section after such amendment, and, if any difficulty`
  line `arises in continuing the said proceedings, the Board may issue (whether by way of modification, not`
  line `affecting the substance, of any rule in this Schedule or otherwise) general or special orders which appear`
  line `to it to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty.]`
  line `1. Restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 as “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989) and Subs. by s. 54, ibid (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 124 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 54, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
