  line 852
  line `THE THIRD SCHEDULE`
  line `P ROCEDURE FOR DISTRAINT BY 1 [ ASSESSING OFFICER ]`
  line `2 [ OR TAX RECOVERY OFFICER ]`
  line `[ See section 226( 5 )]`
  line `Distraint and sale. — Where any distraint and sale of movable property are to be effected by any`
  line `1 [Assessing Officer] 2 [or Tax Recovery Officer] authorised for the purpose, such distraint and sale`
  line `shall be made, as far as may be, in the same manner as attachment and sale of any movable property`
  line `attachable by actual seizure, and the provisions of the Second Schedule relating to attachment and`
  line `sale shall, so far as may be, apply in respect of such distraint and sale.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 55, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 55, ibid (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
