  title `Page 853`
  content obj_root_law_sections_853_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_853_footnotes
  sourcePage 853
obj_root_law_sections_853_content:
  string
  line 853
  line `THE FOURTH SCHEDULE`
  line `PART A`
  line `R ECOGNISED PROVIDENT FUNDS`
  line `[ See sections 2( 38 ), 10( 12 ), 10( 25 ), 36(1)( iv ), 88(2)( vi ), 111, 192(4)]`
  line `1. Application of Part. — This Part shall not apply to any provident fund to which the Provident`
  line `Funds Act, 1925 (19 of 1925), applies.`
  line `2. Definitions. — In this Part, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “employer” means any person who maintains a provident fund for the benefit of his or its`
  line `employees, being —`
  line `( i ) a Hindu undivided family, company, firm or other association of persons, or`
  line `( ii ) an individual engaged in a business or profession the profits and gains whereof are`
  line `assessable to income- tax under the head “Profits and gains of business or profession”;`
  line `( b ) “employee” means an employee participating in a provident fund, but do es not include a`
  line `personal or domestic servant;`
  line `( c ) “contribution” means any sum credited by or on behalf of any employee out of his salary, or`
  line `by an employer out of his own moneys, to the individual account of an employee, but does not`
  line `include any sum credited as interest;`
  line `( d ) “balance to the credit of an employee” means the total amount to the credit of his individual`
  line `account in a provident fund at any time;`
  line `( e ) “annual accretion”, in relation to the balance to the credit of an employee, means the increase`
  line `to such balance in any year, arising from contributions and interest;`
  line `( f ) “accumulated balance due to an employee” means the balance to his credit, or such portion`
  line `thereof as may be claimable by him under the regulations of the fund, on the day he ceases to be an`
  line `employee of the employer maintaining the fund;`
  line `( g ) “regulations of a fund” means the special body of regulations governing the constitution and`
  line `administration of a particular provident fund; and`
  line `( h ) “salary” includes dearness allowance, if the ter ms of employment so provide, but excludes all`
  line `other allowances and perquisites.`
  line `3. According and withdrawal of recognition. — ( 1 ) The 1 [ 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner] or 3 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] may accord recognition to any provident`
  line `fund which, in his opinion, satisfies the conditions prescribed in rule 4 and the rules made by the Board in`
  line `this behalf, and may, at any time, withdraw such recognition if, in his opinion, the provident fund`
  line `contravenes any of those conditions:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_853_footnotes:
