  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_854_footnotes
  sourcePage 854
obj_root_law_sections_854_content:
  string
  line 854
  line `1 [Provided that in a case where recognition has been accorded to any provident fund on or before the`
  line `31st day of March, 2006 and such provident fund does not satisfy the conditions set out in clause ( ea ) of`
  line `rule 4, the recognition to such fund shall be withdrawn, if such fund does not satisfy, on or before`
  line `the 2 [ 3 [31st day of March, 2014]], the conditions set out in the said clause and any other condition which`
  line `the Board may, by rules specify, in this behalf:]`
  line `4 [Provided further that nothing contained in the first proviso shall apply to the provident fund of an`
  line `establishment in respect of which a notification has been issued by the Central Government under`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 16 of the Employees’ Provident Funds and Miscel laneous Provisions Act, 1952`
  line `(19 of 1952).]`
  line `( 2 ) An order according recognition shall take effect on such date as the 5 [ 6 [Principal Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 7 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] may fix in`
  line `accordance with any rules the Board may make in this behalf, such date not being later than the last day`
  line `of the financial year in which the order is made.`
  line `( 3 ) An order withdrawing recognition shall take effect from the date on which it is made.`
  line `( 4 ) An order according recognition to a provident fund shall not, unless the 5 [ 6 [Principal Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 7 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] otherwise`
  line `directs, be affected by the fact that the fund is subsequently amalgamated with another provident fund on`
  line `the occurrence of an amalgamation of the undertakings in connection with which the two funds are`
  line `maintained, or that it subsequently absorbs the whole or a part of another provident fund belonging to an`
  line `undertaking which is wholly or in part transferred to or merged in the undertaking of the employer`
  line `maintaining the first-mentioned fund.`
  line `4. Conditions to be satisfied by recognised provident funds. — In order that a provident fund may`
  line `receive and retain recognition, it shall, subject to the provisions of rule 5, satisfy the conditions set out`
  line `below and any other conditions which the Board may, by rules, specify —`
  line `( a ) all employees shall be employed in India, or shall be employed by an employer whose`
  line `principal place of business is in India;`
  line `( b ) the contributions of an employee in any year shall be a definite proportion of his salary for`
  line `that year, and shall be deducted by the employer from the employee’s salary in that proportion, at`
  line `each periodical payment of such salary in that year, and credited to the employee's individual account`
  line `in the fund;`
  line `( c ) the contributions of an employer to the individual account of an employee in any year shall`
  line `not exceed the amount of the contributions of the employee in that year, and shall be credited to the`
  line `employee's individual account at intervals not exceeding one year;`
  line `( d ) the fund shall be vested in two or more trustees or in the Official Trustee under a trust which`
  line `shall not be revocable, save with the consent of all the beneficiaries;`
  line `( e ) the fund shall consist of contributions as above specified, received by the trustees, of`
  line `accumulations thereof, and of interest credited in respect of such contributions and accumulations,`
  line `and of securities purchased therewith and of any capital gains arising from the transfer of capital`
  line `assets of the fund, and of no other sums;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 56 (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 34, for “31st day of December, 2010” (w.e.f. 1 -1-2011).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 60, for “31st day of March, 2013” (w.e.f. 1 -4- 2013). Earlier “the 31st day of March, 2012”`
  line `was substituted for “the 31st day of March, 2013” by Act 23 of 2012, s. 114 (w.e.f. 1 -4-2012).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 82 (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_854_footnotes:
