  content obj_root_law_sections_855_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_855_footnotes
  sourcePage 855
obj_root_law_sections_855_content:
  string
  line 855
  line `1 [( ea ) the fund shall be a fund of an establishment to which the provisions of sub-section ( 3 ) of`
  line `section 1 of the Employees’ Provident Funds and Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1952 (19 of 1952)`
  line `apply or of an establishment which has been notified by the Central Provident Fund Commissioner`
  line `under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 1 of the said Act, and such establishment shall obtain exemption`
  line `under section 17 of the said Act from the operation of all or any of the provisions of any scheme`
  line `referred to in that section;]`
  line `( f ) the employer shall not be entitled to recover any sum whatsoever from the fund, save in cases`
  line `where the employee is dismissed for misconduct or voluntarily leaves his employment otherwise than`
  line `on account of ill-health or other unavoidable cause before the expiration of the term of service`
  line `specified in this behalf in the regulations of the fund:`
  line `Provided that in such cases the recoveries made by the employer shall be limited to the`
  line `contributions made by him to the individual account of the employee, and to interest credited in`
  line `respect of such contributions in accordance with the regulations of the fund and the accumulations`
  line thereof;
  line `( g ) the accumulated balance due to an employee shall be payable on the day he ceases to be an`
  line `employee of the employer maintaining the fund;`
  line `( h ) save as provided in clause ( g ) or in accordance with such conditions and restrictions as the`
  line `Board may, by rules, specify, no portion of the balance to the credit of an employee shall be payable`
  line `to him.`
  line `5. Relaxation of conditions. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in clause ( a ) of rule 4, the`
  line `2 [ 3 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 4 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner]] may, if he thinks fit and subject to such conditions, if any, as he thinks proper to attach to`
  line `the recognition, accord recognition to a fund maintained by an employer whose principal place of`
  line `business is not in India, provided the proportion of employees employed outside India does not exceed ten`
  line `per cent.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in clause ( b ) of rule 4, an employee who retains his`
  line `employment while serving in the armed forces of the Union or when taken into or employed in the`
  line `national service under any law for the time being in force, may, whether he receives from the employer`
  line `any salary or not, contribute to the fund during his service in the armed forces of the Union or while so`
  line `taken into or employed in the national service a sum not exceeding the amount he would have contributed`
  line `had he continued to serve the employer.`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in clause ( e ) or clause ( g ) of rule 4, —`
  line `( a ) at the request made in writing by the employee who ceases to be an employee of the employer`
  line `maintaining the fund, the trustees of the fund may consent to retain the whole or any part of the`
  line `accumulated balance due to the employee to be drawn by him at any time on demand;`
  line `( b ) where the accumulated balance due to an employee who has ceased to be an employee is`
  line `retained in the fund in accordance with the preceding clause, the fund may consist also of interest in`
  line `respect of such accumulated balance;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 82, for clause ( ea ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2007).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_855_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_856:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-856
  sectionNo (856)
  orderNo 856
  title `Page 856`
  content obj_root_law_sections_856_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_856_footnotes
  sourcePage 856
obj_root_law_sections_856_content:
  string
  line 856
  line `1 [( c ) the fund may also consist of any amount transferred from the individual account of an`
  line `employee in any recognised provident fund maintained by his former employer and the interest in`
  line `respect thereof.]`
  line `( 4 ) Subject to any rules which the Board may make in this behalf, the 2 [ 3 [Principal Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] may, in respect`
  line `of any particular fund, relax the provisions of clause ( c ) of rule 4, —`
  line `( a ) so as to permit the payment of larger contributions by an employer to the individual accounts`
  line `of employees whose salaries do not in each case exceed five hundred rupees per mensem; and`
  line `( b ) so as to permit the crediting by employers to the individual accounts of employees of`
  line `periodical bonuses or other contributions of a contingent nature, where the calculation and payment`
  line `of such bonuses or other contributions is provided for on definite principles by the regulations of the`
  line fund.
  line `( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in clause ( h ) of rule 4, in order to enable an employee to pay`
  line `the amount of tax assessed on his total income as determined under sub-rule ( 4 ) of rule 11, he shall be`
  line `entitled to withdraw from the balance to his credit in the recognised provident fund a sum not exceeding`
  line `the difference between such amount and the amount to which he would have been assessed if the`
  line `transferred balance referred to in sub-rule ( 2 ) of rule 11 had not been included in his total income.`
  line `6. Employer’s annual contributions, when deemed to be income received by employee. — That`
  line `portion of the annual accretion in any previous year to the balance at the credit of an employee`
  line `participating in a recognised provident fund as consists of —`
  line `( a ) contributions made by the employer in excess of 5 [twelve] per cent. of the salary of the`
  line `employee, and`
  line `( b ) interest credited on the balance to the credit of the employee in so far as it 6 *** is allowed at a`
  line `rate exceeding such rate as may be fixed by the Central Government in this behalf by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette,`
  line `shall be deemed to have been received by the employee in that previous year and shall be included in his`
  line `total income for that previous year, and shall be liable to income-tax 7 ***.`
  line `8 [ 7. Exemption for employee’s contributions. — An employee participating in a recognised`
  line `provident fund shall, in respect of his own contributions to his individual account in the fund in the`
  line `previous year, be entitled to a deduction in the computation of his total income of an amount determined`
  line `in accordance with 9 [section 80C ].]`
  line `8. Exclusion from total income of accumulated balance. — The accumulated balance due and`
  line `becoming payable to an employee participating in a recognised provident fund shall be excluded from the`
  line `computation of his total income —`
  line `( i ) if he has rendered continuous service with his employer for a period of five years or more, or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 1974, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 26 of 1997, s. 58, for “ten” (w.e.f. 1-4-1998).`
  line `6. The words “exceeds one - third of the salary of the employee or” omitted by Act 44 of 1980, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1981).`
  line `7. The words “and super - tax” omitted by Act 10 of 1965, s. 66 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 66, ibid, for rule 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 20, for “section 80A or, as the case may be, to a deduction from the amount of income -tax`
  line `with which he is chargeable on his total income of an amount of income- tax determined in accordance with section 87”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1968).`
obj_root_law_sections_856_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_857:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-857
  sectionNo (857)
  orderNo 857
  title `Page 857`
  content obj_root_law_sections_857_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_857_footnotes
  sourcePage 857
obj_root_law_sections_857_content:
  string
  line 857
  line `( ii ) if, though he has not rendered such continuous service, the service has been terminated by`
  line `reason of the employ ee’s ill -health, or by the contraction or discontinuance of the employer's business`
  line `or other cause beyond the control of the employee, 1 [or]`
  line `1 [( iii ) if, on the cessation of his employment, the employee obtains employment with any other`
  line `employer, to the extent the accumulated balance due and becoming payable to him is transferred to`
  line `his individual account in any recognised provident fund maintained by 2 [such other employer; or]`
  line `3 [( iv ) if the entire balance standing to the credit of the employee is transferred to his account`
  line `under a pension scheme referred to in section 80CCD and notified by the Central Government.]`
  line `Explanation. — Where the accumulated balance due and becoming payable to an employee`
  line `participating in a recognised provident fund maintained by his employer includes any amount`
  line `transferred from his individual account in any other recognised provident fund or funds maintained by`
  line `his former employer or employers, then, in computing the period of continuous service for the`
  line `purposes of clause ( i ) or clause ( ii ) the period or periods for which such employee rendered`
  line `continuous service under his former employer or employers aforesaid shall be included.]`
  line `9. Tax on accumulated balance. — ( 1 ) Where the accumulated balance due to an employee`
  line `participating in a recognised provident fund is included in his total income owing to the provisions of`
  line `rule 8 not being applicable, the 4 [Assessing Officer] shall calculate the total of the various sums of`
  line `5 [tax] which would have been payable by the employee in respect of his total income for each of the`
  line `years concerned if the fund had not been a recognised provident fund, and the amount by which such`
  line `total exceeds the total of all sums paid by or on behalf of such employee by way of 5 [tax] for such`
  line `years shall be payable by the employee in addition to any other 5 [tax] for which he may be liable for`
  line `the previous year in which the accumulated balance due to him becomes payable.`
  line `( 2 ) Where the accumulated balance due to an employee participating in a recognised provident fund`
  line `which is not included in his total income under the provisions of rule 8 becomes payable, an amount equal`
  line `to the aggregate of the amounts of super-tax on annual accretions that would have been payable under`
  line `section 58E of the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922), for any assessment year up to and including`
  line `the assessment year 1932-33, if the Indian Income-tax (Second Amendment) Act, 1933 (18 of 1933), had`
  line `come into force on the 15th day of March, 1930, shall be payable by the employee in addition to any`
  line `other tax payable by him for the previous year in which such balance becomes payable.`
  line `10. Deduction at source of tax payable on accumulated balance. — The trustees of a recognised`
  line `provident fund, or any person authorised by the regulations of the fund to make payment of accumulated`
  line `balances due to employees, shall, in cases where sub-rule ( 1 ) of rule 9 applies, at the time an accumulated`
  line `balance due to an employee is paid, deduct therefrom the amount payable under that rule and all the`
  line `provisions of Chapter XVII-B shall apply as if the accumulated balance were income chargeable under`
  line `the head “Salaries”.`
  line `11. Treatment of balance in newly recognised provident fund. — ( 1 ) Where recognition is accorded`
  line `to a provident fund with existing balances, an account shall be made of the fund up to the day`
  line `immediately preceding the day on which the recognition takes effect, showing the balance to the credit of`
  line `each employee on such day, and containing such further particulars as the Board may prescribe.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 1974, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-4-1975).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 115, for “such other employer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2017).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 115, ibid (w.e.f. 1-4-2017).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e. f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 66, for “income - tax and super tax” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
obj_root_law_sections_857_footnotes:
