  line
obj_root_law_sections_858:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-858
  sectionNo (858)
  orderNo 858
  title `Page 858`
  content obj_root_law_sections_858_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_858_footnotes
  sourcePage 858
obj_root_law_sections_858_content:
  string
  line 858
  line `( 2 ) The account shall also show in respect of the balance to the credit of each employee the amount`
  line `thereof which is to be transferred to that employee’s account in the recognised provident fund, and such`
  line `amount (hereinafter called his transferred balance) shall be shown as the balance to his credit in the`
  line `recognised provident fund on the date on which the recognition of the fund takes effect, and sub-rule ( 4 )`
  line `of this rule and sub-rule ( 5 ) of rule 5 shall apply thereto.`
  line `( 3 ) Any portion of the balance to the credit of an employee in the existing fund which is not`
  line `transferred to the recognised fund shall be excluded from the accounts of the recognised fund and shall be`
  line `liable to income-tax 1 *** in accordance with the provisions of this Act, other than this Part.`
  line `( 4 ) Subject to such rules as the Board may make in this behalf, the 2 [Assessing Officer] shall make a`
  line `calculation of the aggregate of all sums comprised in a transferred balance which would have been liable`
  line `to income-tax if this Part had been in force from the date of the institution of the fund, without regard to`
  line `any tax which may have been paid on any sum, and such aggregate (if any) shall be deemed to be income`
  line `received by the employee in the previous year in which the recognition of the fund takes effect and shall`
  line `be included in the employee’s total income for that previous year, and, for the purposes of assessment, the`
  line `remainder of the transferred balance shall be disregarded, but no other exemption or relief, by way of`
  line `refund or otherwise, shall be granted in respect of any sum comprised in such transferred balance:`
  line `Provided that, in cases of serious accounting difficulty, the 3 [ 4 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner] or 5 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] may, subject to the said rules, make a`
  line `summary calculation of such aggregate.`
  line `( 5 ) Nothing in this rule shall affect the rights of the persons administering an unrecognised provident`
  line `fund or dealing with it, or with the balance to the credit of any individual employee before recognition is`
  line `accorded, in any manner which may be lawful.`
  line `12. Accounts of recognised provident funds. — ( 1 ) The accounts of a recognised provident fund`
  line `shall be maintained by the trustees of the fund and shall be in such form and for such periods, and shall`
  line `contain such particulars, as the Board may prescribe.`
  line `( 2 ) The accounts shall be open to inspection at all reasonable times by income-tax authorities, and the`
  line `trustees shall furnish to the 2 [Assessing Officer] such abstracts thereof as the Board may prescribe.`
  line `13. Appeals. — ( 1 ) An employer objecting to an order of the 3 [ 4 [Principal Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Chief Commissioner] or 5 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] refusing to recognise or an order`
  line `withdrawing recognition from a provident fund may appeal, within sixty days of such order, to the Board.`
  line `( 2 ) The appeal shall be in such form and shall be verified in such manner and shall be subject to the`
  line `payment of such fee as the Board may prescribe.`
  line `1. The words “and super - tax” omitted by Act 10 of 1965, s. 66 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4, for “Chief Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_858_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_859:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-859
  sectionNo (859)
  orderNo 859
  title `Page 859`
  content obj_root_law_sections_859_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_859_footnotes
  sourcePage 859
obj_root_law_sections_859_content:
  string
  line 859
  line `14. Treatment of fund transferred by employer to trustee. — ( 1 ) Where an employer, who`
  line `maintains a provident fund (whether recognised or not) for the benefit of his employees and has not`
  line `transferred the fund or any portion of it, transfers such fund or portion to trustees in trust for the`
  line `employees participating in the fund, the amount so transferred shall be deemed to be of the nature of`
  line `capital expenditure.`
  line `( 2 ) When an employee participating in such fund is paid the accumulated balance due to him`
  line `therefrom, any portion of such balance as represents his share in the amount so transferred to the trustees`
  line `(without addition of interest, and exclusive of the employee's contributions and interest thereon) shall, if`
  line `the employer has made effective arrangements to secure that tax shall be deducted at source from the`
  line `amount of such share when paid to the employee, be deemed to be an expenditure by the employer within`
  line `the meaning of section 37, incurred in the previous year in which the accumulated balance due to the`
  line `employee is paid.`
  line `15. Provisions relating to rules. — ( 1 ) In addition to any power conferred by this Part, the Board may`
  line `make rules —`
  line `( a ) prescribing the statements and other information to be submitted along with an application for`
  line recognition;
  line `( b ) limiting the contributions to a recognised provident fund by employees of a company who are`
  line `shareholders in the company;`
  line `1 [( bb ) regulating the investment or deposit of the moneys of a recognised provident fund:`
  line `Provided that no rule made under this clause shall require the investment of more than fifty per`
  line `cent. of the moneys of such fund in Government securities as defined in section 2 of the Public Debt`
  line `Act, 1944 (18 of 1944);]`
  line `( c ) providing for the assessment by way of penalty of any consideration received by an employee`
  line `for an assignment of, or creation of a charge upon, his beneficial interest in a recognised provident`
  line fund;
  line `( d ) determining the extent to and the manner in which exemption from payment of 2 [tax] may be`
  line `granted in respect of contributions and interest credited to the individual accounts of employees in a`
  line `provident fund from which recognition has been withdrawn; and`
  line `( e ) generally, to carry out the purposes of this Part and to secure such further control over the`
  line `recognition of provident funds and the administration of recognised provident funds as it may deem`
  line requisite.
  line `( 2 ) All rules made under this Part shall be subject to the provisions of section 296.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 57 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 66, for “income -tax and super- tax” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
