obj_root_law_sections_860:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-860
  sectionNo (860)
  orderNo 860
  title `Page 860`
  content obj_root_law_sections_860_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_860_footnotes
  sourcePage 860
obj_root_law_sections_860_content:
  string
  line 860
  line `PART B`
  line _______
  line `A PPROVED SUPERANNUATION FUNDS`
  line `[ See sections 2( 6 ), 10( 13 ), 10( 25 ) ( iii ), 36(1)( iv ), 87(1)( e ), 192(5), 1 [206]]`
  line `1. Definitions. — In this Part, unless the context otherwise requires, “employer”, “employee”,`
  line `“contribution” and “salary” have, in relation to superannuation funds, the meanings assigned to those`
  line `expressions in rule 2 of Part A in relation to provident funds.`
  line `2. Approval and withdrawal of approval. — ( 1 ) The 2 [ 3 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner] or 4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] may accord approval to any`
  line `superannuation fund or any part of a superannuation fund which, in his opinion, complies with the`
  line `requirements of rule 3, and may at any time withdraw such approval, if, in his opinion, the circumstances`
  line `of the fund or part cease to warrant the continuance of the approval.`
  line `( 2 ) The 2 [ 3 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 4 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner]] shall communicate in writing to the trustees of the fund the grant of approval with the`
  line `date on which the approval is to take effect, and, where the approval is granted subject to conditions,`
  line `those conditions.`
  line `( 3 ) The 2 [ 3 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner or 4 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner]] shall communicate in writing to the trustees of the fund any withdrawal of approval with`
  line `the reasons for such withdrawal and the date on which the withdrawal is to take effect.`
  line `( 4 ) The 2 [ 3 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner or 4 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner]] shall neither refuse nor withdraw approval to any superannuation fund or any part of a`
  line `superannuation fund unless he has given the trustees of that fund a reasonable opportunity of being heard`
  line `in the matter.`
  line `3. Conditions for approval. — In order that a superannuation fund may receive and retain approval,`
  line `it shall satisfy the conditions set out below and any other conditions which the Board may, by rules,`
  line `prescribe —`
  line `( a ) the fund shall be a fund established under an irrevocable trust in connection with a trade or`
  line `undertaking carried on in India, and not less than ninety per cent of the employees shall be employed`
  line `in India;`
  line `( b ) the fund shall have for its sole purpose the provision of annuities for employees in the trade or`
  line `undertaking on their retirement at or after a specified age or on their becoming incapacitated prior to`
  line `such retirement, or for the widows, children or dependants of persons who are or have been such`
  line `employees on the death of those persons;`
  line `( c ) the employer in the trade or undertaking shall be a contributor to the fund; and`
  line `( d ) all annuities, pensions and other benefits granted from the fund shall be payable only in India.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 74, for “206( 2 )” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1987).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4 for “Chief Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_860_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_861:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-861
  sectionNo (861)
