  title `Page 861`
  content obj_root_law_sections_861_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_861_footnotes
  sourcePage 861
obj_root_law_sections_861_content:
  string
  line 861
  line `4. Application for approval. — ( 1 ) An application for approval of a superannuation fund or part of a`
  line `superannuation fund shall be made in writing by the trustees of the fund to the 1 [Assessing Officer] by`
  line `whom the employer is assessable, and shall be accompanied by a copy of the instrument under which the`
  line `fund is established and by two copies of the rules 2 [and, where the fund has been in existence during any`
  line `year or years prior to the financial year in which the application for approval is made, also two copies of`
  line `the accounts of the fund relating to such prior year or years (not being more than three years immediately`
  line `preceding the year in which the said application is made)] for which such accounts have been made up,`
  line `but the 3 [ 4 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 5 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner]] may require such further information to be supplied as he thinks proper.`
  line `( 2 ) If any alteration in the rules, constitution, objects or conditions of the fund is made at any time`
  line `after the date of the application for approval, the trustees of the fund shall forthwith communicate such`
  line `alteration to the 1 [Assessing Officer] mentioned in sub-rule ( 1 ), and in default of such communication any`
  line `approval given shall, unless the 3 [ 4 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 5 [Principal`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner]] otherwise orders, be deemed to have been withdrawn from the date on`
  line `which the alteration took effect.`
  line `5. Contributions by employer when deemed to be income of employer. — Where any contributions`
  line `by an employer (including the interest thereon, if any) are repaid to the employer, the amount so repaid`
  line `shall be deemed for the purpose of income-tax 6 *** to be the income of the employer of the previous year`
  line `in which it is so repaid.`
  line `6. Deduction of tax on contributions paid to an employee. — Where any contributions made by an`
  line `employer, including interest on contributions, if any, are paid to an employee during his lifetime 7 [in`
  line `circumstances other than those referred to in clause ( 13 ) of section 10], 8 [tax] on the amounts so paid shall`
  line `be deducted at the average rate of 8 [tax] at which the employee was liable to 8 [tax] during the preceding`
  line `three years or during the period, if less than three years, when he was a member of the fund, and shall be`
  line `paid by the trustees to the credit of the Central Government within the prescribed time and in such`
  line `manner as the Board may direct.`
  line `7. Deduction from pay of and contributions on behalf of employee to be included in`
  line `return. — Where an employer deducts from the emoluments paid to an employee or pays on his behalf`
  line `any contributions of that employee to an approved superannuation fund, he shall include all such`
  line `deductions or payments in the return which he is required to furnish under 9 *** section 206.`
  line `8. Appeals. — ( 1 ) An employer objecting to an order of the 3 [ 4 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner] or 5 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] refusing to accord approval to a`
  line `superannuation fund or an order withdrawing such approval may appeal, within sixty days of such order,`
  line `to the Board.`
  line `( 2 ) The appeal shall be in such form and shall be verified in such manner and shall be subject to the`
  line `payment of such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line `9. Liability of trustees on cessation of approval. — If a fund or a part of a fund for any reason ceases`
  line `to be an approved superannuation fund, the trustees of the fund shall nevertheless remain liable to tax on`
  line `any sum paid on account of returned contributions (including interest on contributions, if any), in so far as`
  line `the sum so paid is in respect of contributions made before the fund or part of the fund ceased to be an`
  line `approved superannuation fund under the provisions of this Part.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 57, for “and of the accounts of the fund for the last three years for which such accounts have`
  line `been made up” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1971).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4 for “Chief Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `6. The words “and super - tax” omitted by Act 10 of 1965, s. 66 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
  line `7. Ins. by s. 66, ibid, (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 66, ibid., for “income -tax and super- tax” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
  line `9. The words, brackets and figure “sub -section ( 1 ) of” omitted by Act 11 of 1987 s. 74 (w.e.f. 1 -6-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_861_footnotes:
  string
