  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_862_footnotes
  sourcePage 862
obj_root_law_sections_862_content:
  string
  line 862
  line `10. Particulars to be furnished in respect of superannuation funds. — The trustees of an approved`
  line `superannuation fund and any employer who contributes to an approved superannuation fund shall, when`
  line `required by notice from the 1 [Assessing Officer], within such period, not being less than twenty-one days`
  line `from the date of the notice, as may be specified in the notice, furnish such return, statement, particulars or`
  line `information, as the 1 [Assessing Officer] may require.`
  line `11. Provisions relating to rules. — ( 1 ) In addition to any power conferred by this Part, the Board may`
  line `make rules —`
  line `( a ) prescribing the statements and other information to be submitted along with an application for`
  line approval;
  line `( b ) prescribing the returns, statements, particulars, or information which the 1 [Assessing Officer]`
  line `may require from the trustees of an approved superannuation fund or from the employer;`
  line `( c ) limiting the ordinary annual contribution and any other contributions to an approved`
  line `superannuation fund by an employer;`
  line `2 [( cc ) regulating the investment or deposit of the moneys of an approved superannuation fund:`
  line `Provided that no rule made under this clause shall require the investment of more than fifty per`
  line `cent of the moneys of such fund in Government securities as defined in section 2 of the Public Debt`
  line `Act, 1944 (18 of 1944);]`
  line `( d ) providing for the assessment by way of penalty of any consideration received by an employee`
  line `for an assignment of, or creation of a charge upon, his beneficial interest in an approved`
  line `superannuation fund;`
  line `( e ) determining the extent to, and the manner in, which exemption from payment of 3 [tax] may be`
  line `granted in respect of any payment made from a superannuation fund from which approval has been`
  line withdrawn;
  line `( f ) providing for the withdrawal of approval in the case of a fund which ceases to satisfy the`
  line `requirements of this Part or of the rules made thereunder; and`
  line `( g ) generally, to carry out the purposes of this Part and to secure such further control over the`
  line `approval of the superannuation funds and the administration of approved superannuation funds as it`
  line `may deem requisite.`
  line `( 2 ) All rules made under this Part shall be subject to the provisions of section 296.`
  line `PART C`
  line `A PPROVED GRATUITY FUND`
  line `4 [ See sections 2( 5 ), 10( 25 )( iv ), 17( 1 )( iii ), 36( 1 )( v )]`
  line `1. Definitions. —In this Part, unless the context otherwise requires “employer”, “employee”,`
  line `“contribution” and “salary” have, in relation to gratuity funds, the meanings assigned to those expressions`
  line `in rule 2 of Part A in relation to provident funds.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 57 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `3. Subs by Act 10 of 1965, s. 66 for “income -tax and super- tax” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 42 for “ See sections 2( 5 ), 17( 1 )( iii ), 36 ( 1 )( v )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1973).`
