obj_root_law_sections_863_content:
  string
  line 863
  line `2. Approval and withdrawal of approval. — ( 1 ) The 1 [ 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner] or 3 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] may accord approval to any gratuity fund`
  line `which, in his opinion, complies with the requirements of rule 3 and may at any time withdraw such`
  line `approval if, in his opinion, the circumstances of the fund cease to warrant the continuance of the approval.`
  line `( 2 ) The 1 [ 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 3 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner]] shall communicate in writing to the trustees of the fund the grant of approval with the`
  line `date on which the approval is to take effect and where the approval is granted subject to conditions, those`
  line conditions.
  line `( 3 ) The 1 [ 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 3 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner]] shall communicate in writing to the trustees of the fund any withdrawal of approval with`
  line `the reasons for such withdrawal and the date on which the withdrawal is to take effect.`
  line `( 4 ) The 1 [ 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 3 [Principal Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner]] shall neither refuse nor withdraw approval to any gratuity fund unless he has given the`
  line `trustees of that fund a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
  line `3. Conditions for approval. — In order that a gratuity fund may receive and retain approval, it shall`
  line `satisfy the conditions set out below and any other conditions which the Board may, by rules, prescribe —`
  line `( a ) the fund shall be a fund established under an irrevocable trust in connection with a trade or`
  line `undertaking carried on in India, and not less than ninety per cent of the employees shall be employed`
  line `in India;`
  line `( b ) the fund shall have for its sole purpose the provision of a gratuity to employees in the trade or`
  line `undertaking on their retirement at or after a specified age or on their becoming incapacitated prior to`
  line `such retirement or on termination of their employment after a minimum period of service specified in`
  line `the rules of the fund or to the widows, children or dependants of such employees on their death;`
  line `( c ) the employer in the trade or undertaking shall be a contributor to the fund; and`
  line `( d ) all benefits granted by the fund shall be payable only in India.`
  line `4. Application for approval. — ( 1 ) An application for approval of a gratuity fund shall be made in`
  line `writing by the trustees of the fund to the 4 [Assessing Officer], by whom the employer is assessable and`
  line `shall be accompanied by a copy of the instrument under which the fund is established and by two copies`
  line `of the rules 5 [and, where the fund has been in existence during any year or years prior to the financial year`
  line `in which the application for approval is made, also two copies of the accounts of the fund relating to such`
  line `prior year or years (not being more than three years immediately preceding the year in which the said`
  line `application is made) for which such accounts have been made up], but the 1 [ 2 [Principal Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or 3 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] may require such`
  line `further information to be supplied as he thinks proper.`
  line `( 2 ) If any alteration in the rules, constitution, objects or conditions of the fund is made at any time`
  line `after the date of the application for approval, the trustees of the fund shall forthwith communicate such`
  line `alterations to the 4 [Assessing Officer] mentioned in sub-rule ( 1 ), and in default of such communication,`
  line `any approval given shall, unless the 1 [ 2 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief Commissioner] or`
  line `3 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] otherwise orders, be deemed to have been withdrawn from`
  line `the date on which the alteration took effect.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4 for “Chief Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs by Act 42 of 1970, s. 57, for “and of the accounts of the fund for the last year for which such accounts have been`
  line `made up” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1971).`
