  content obj_root_law_sections_864_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_864_footnotes
  sourcePage 864
obj_root_law_sections_864_content:
  string
  line 864
  line `5. Gratuity deemed to be salary. — Where any gratuity is paid to an employee during his lifetime,`
  line `the gratuity shall be treated as salary paid to the employee for the purposes of this Act.`
  line `6. Liability of trustees on cessation of approval. — If a gratuity fund for any reason ceases to be an`
  line `approved gratuity fund, the trustees of the fund shall nevertheless remain liable to tax on any gratuity paid`
  line `to any employee.`
  line `7. contributions by employer, when deemed to be income of employer. — Where any`
  line `contributions by an employer (including the interest thereon, if any) are repaid to the employer, the`
  line `amount so repaid shall be deemed for the purposes of income-tax 1 *** to be the income of the employer`
  line `of the previous year in which they are so repaid.`
  line `8. Appeals. — ( 1 ) An employer objecting to an order of the 2 [ 3 [Principal Chief Commissioner or Chief`
  line `Commissioner] or 4 [Principal Commissioner or Commissioner]] refusing to accord approval to a gratuity`
  line `fund or an order withdrawing such approval may appeal, within sixty days of such order, to the Board.`
  line `( 2 ) The appeal shall be in such form and shall be verified in such manner and shall be subject to the`
  line `payment of such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line `5 [ 8A. Particulars to be furnished in respect of gratuity funds. — The trustees of an approved`
  line `gratuity fund and any employer who contributes to an approved gratuity fund shall, when required by`
  line `notice from the 6 [Assessing Officer], furnish within such period, not being less than twenty-one days from`
  line `the date of the notice, as may be specified in the notice, such return, statement, particulars or information,`
  line `as the 6 [Assessing Officer] may require.]`
  line `9. Provisions relating to rules. — ( 1 ) In addition to any power conferred in this Part, the Board may`
  line `make rules —`
  line `( a ) prescribing the statements and other information to be submitted along with an application for`
  line approval;
  line `( b ) limiting the ordinary annual and other contributions of an employer to the fund;`
  line `7 [( bb ) regulating the investment or deposit of the moneys of an approved gratuity fund:`
  line `Provided that no rule made under this clause shall require the investment of more than fifty per`
  line `cent of the moneys of such fund in Government securities as defined in section 2 of the Public Debt`
  line `Act, 1944 (18 of 1944);]`
  line `( c ) providing for the assessment by way of penalty of any consideration received by an employee`
  line `for an assignment of, or the creation of a charge upon, his beneficial interest in an approved gratuity`
  line fund;
  line `( d ) providing for the withdrawal of the approval in the case of a fund which ceases to satisfy the`
  line `requirements of this Part or the rules made thereunder; and`
  line `( e ) generally, to carry out the purposes of this Part and to secure such further control over the`
  line `approval of gratuity funds and the administration of gratuity funds as it may deem requisite.`
  line `( 2 ) All rules made under this Part shall be subject to the provisions of section 296.`
  line `1. The words “and super - tax” omitted by Act 10 of 1965, s. 66 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 4 for “Chief Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-2013).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 57 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 2, for “Income - tax” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 57 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
