obj_root_law_sections_865_content:
  string
  line 865
  line `1 [THE FIFTH SCHEDULE`
  line `2 [ See section 33( 1 )( b )( B )( i )]]`
  line `L IST OF ARTICLES AND THINGS`
  line `( 1 ) Iron and steel (metal), ferro-alloys and special steels.`
  line `( 2 ) Aluminium, copper, lead and zinc (metals).`
  line `( 3 ) 3 [Coal, lignite, iron ore], bauxite, manganese ore, dolomite, limestone, magnesite and mineral oil.`
  line `( 4 ) Industrial machinery specified under the heading "8. Industrial machinery", sub-heading "A.`
  line `Major items of specialised equipment used in specific industries", of the First Schedule to the Industries`
  line `(Development and Regulation) Act, 1951 (65 of 1951).`
  line `( 5 ) Boilers and steam generating plants, steam engines and turbines and internal combustion engines.`
  line `( 6 ) Flame and drip proof motors.`
  line `( 7 ) Equipment for the generation and transmission of electricity including transformers, cables and`
  line `transmission towers.`
  line `( 8 ) Machine tools and precision tools (including their attachments and accessories, cutting tools and`
  line `small tools), dies and jigs.`
  line `( 9 ) Tractors, earth-moving machinery and agricultural implements.`
  line `( 10 ) Motor trucks and buses.`
  line `( 11 ) Steel castings and forgings and malleable iron and steel castings.`
  line `( 12 ) Cement and refractories.`
  line `( 13 ) Fertilisers, namely, ammonium sulphate, ammonium sulphate nitrate (double salt), ammonium`
  line `nitrate, calcium ammonium nitrate (nitrolime stone), ammonium chloride, superphosphate, urea and`
  line `complex fertilisers of synthetic origin containing both nitrogen and phosphorus, such as ammonium`
  line `phosphates, ammonium sulphate phosphate and ammo-nium nitro phosphate.`
  line `( 14 ) Soda ash.`
  line `( 15 ) Pesticides.`
  line `( 16 ) Paper and pulp including newsprint.`
  line `( 17 ) Electronic equipment, namely, radar equipment, computers, electronic accounting and business`
  line `machines, electronic communication equipment, electronic control instruments and basic components,`
  line `such as valves, transistors, resistors, condensers, coils, magnetic materials and microwave components.`
  line `( 18 ) Petrochemicals including corresponding products manufactured from other basic raw materials`
  line `like calcium carbide, ethyl alcohol or hydrocarbons from other sources.`
  line `( 19 ) Ships.`
  line `( 20 ) Automobile ancillaries.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 67 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 19 of 1968, s. 30 and the Third Schedule, for “[ See sections 33(1)(b)(B)(i) and 80B(7)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1969).`
  line `Earlier substituted by Act 20 of 1967, s. 33 and the Third Schedule, for"[ See sections 33(1)(b)(B)(i) and 83B(7)” (w.e.f.`
  line `1-4-1968). Prior substituted by Act 13 of 1966, s. 37, for "[ See section 33 (1) ( iii ) (c) I" (w.e.f. 1-4-1966).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 15 of 1965, s. 18, for “Iron ore” (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
