  line `1 [THE SEVENTH SCHEDULE`
  line `[ See section 35E]`
  line `PART A`
  line _________
  line `M INERALS`
  line `1. Aluminium ores.`
  line `2. Apatite and phosphatic ores.`
  line `3. Beryl.`
  line `4. Chrome ore.`
  line `5. Coal and lignite.`
  line `6. Columbite, Samarskite and other minerals of the "rare earths" group.`
  line `7. Copper.`
  line `8. Gold.`
  line `9. Gypsum.`
  line `10. Iron ore.`
  line `11. Lead.`
  line `12. Manganese ore.`
  line `13. Molybdenum.`
  line `14. Nickel ores.`
  line `15. Platinum and other precious metals and their ores.`
  line `16. Pitchblende and other uranium ores.`
  line `17. Precious stones.`
  line `18. Rutile.`
  line `19. Silver.`
  line `20. Sulphur and its ores.`
  line `21. Tin.`
  line `22. Tungsten ores.`
  line `23. Uraniferousallanite, monazite and other thorium minerals.`
  line `24. Uranium bearing tailings left over from ores after extraction of copper and gold, ilmenite and other`
  line `titanium ores.`
  line `25. Vanadium ores.`
  line `26. Zinc.`
  line `27. Zircon.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 58 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
