  line `PART B`
  line `G ROUPS OF ASSOCIATED MINERALS`
  line `1. Apatite, Beryl, Cassiterite, Columbite, Emerald, Felspar, Lepidolite, Mica, Pitchblende, Quartz,`
  line `Samarskite, Scheelite, Topaz, Tantalite, Tourmaline.`
  line `2. Iron, Manganese, Titanium, Vanadium and Nickel minerals.`
  line `3. Lead, Zinc, Copper, Cadmium, Arsenic, Antimony, Bismuth, Cobalt, Nickel, Molybdenum, and`
  line `Uranium minerals, and Gold and Silver, Arsinopyrite, Chalcopyrite, Pyrite, Pyphrotite and`
  line Pentalandite.
  line `4. Chromium, Osmiridium, Platinum and Nickel minerals.`
  line `5. Kyanite, Sillimanite, Corrundum, Dumortierite and Topaz.`
  line `6. Gold, Silver, Tellurium, Selenium and Pyrite.`
  line `7. Barytes, Fluorite, Chalcocite, Selenium, and minerals of Zinc, Lead and Silver.`
  line `8. Tin and Tungsten minerals.`
  line `9. Limestone, Dolomite and Magnesite.`
  line `10. Ilmenite, Monazite, Zircon, Rutile, Garnet and Sillimanite.`
  line `11. Sulphides of Copper and Iron.`
  line `12. Coal, Fireclay and Shale.`
  line `13. Magnetite and Apatite.`
  line `14. Magnesite and Chromite.`
  line `15. Talc (Soapstone and Steatite) and Dolomite.`
  line `16. Bauxite, Laterite, Aluminous Clays, Lithomorge, Titanium, Vanadium, Gallium and Columbium`
  line minerals.]
