obj_root_law_sections_871_content:
  string
  line 871
  line `1 [THE ELEVENTH SCHEDULE`
  line `2 {[ See section 32A, 3 [section 32AB], # section 80CC(3)( a )( i ), section 80-I(2), 4 @ [section 80J(4) and`
  line `$ section 88A(3)( a )( i )]]}`
  line `L IST OF A RTICLES OR T HINGS`
  line `1. Beer, wine and other alcoholic spirits.`
  line `2. Tobacco and tobacco preparations, such as, cigars and cheroots, cigarettes, biris, smoking mixtures`
  line `for pipes and cigarettes, chewing tobacco and snuff.`
  line `3. Cosmetics and toilet preparations.`
  line `4. Tooth paste, dental cream, tooth powder and soap.`
  line `5. Aerated waters in the manufacture of which blended flavouring concentrates in any form are used.`
  line `5 [ Explanation. —“Blended flavouring concentrates” shall include, and shall be deemed always to ha ve`
  line `included, synthetic essences in any form.]`
  line `6. Confectionery and chocolates.`
  line `7. Gramophones, including record-players and gramophone records.`
  line `6 * * * * *`
  line `7 [9. Projectors.]`
  line `10. Photographic apparatus and goods.`
  line `8 * * * * *`
  line `22. Office machines and apparatus such as typewriters, calculating machines, cash registering`
  line `machines, cheque writing machines, intercom machines and teleprinters.`
  line `Explanation. —The expression “office machines and apparatus” includes all machines and apparatus`
  line `used in offices, shops, factories, workshops, educational institutions, railway stations, hotels and`
  line `restaurants for doing office work 9 [and for data processing (not being computers within the meaning`
  line `of section 32AB)].`
  line `23. Steel furniture, whether made partly or wholly of steel.`
  line `24. Safes, strong boxes, cash and deed boxes and strong room doors.`
  line `25. Latex foam sponge and polyurethane foam.`
  line `10 * * * * *`
  line `27. Crown corks, or other fittings of cork, rubber, polyethylene or any other material.`
  line `28. Pilfer-proof caps for packaging or other fittings of cork, rubber, polyethylene or any other`
  line material.
  line `11 * * * * *]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1-4-1978).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 1981, s. 24, for “[ See section 32A and section 80J( 4 )]” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1981).`
  line `# Section 80CC omitted by Act 33 of 1996, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 1986, s. 39 (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 50 for “and section 80(J)(4)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1990).`
  line `@ Now Section 80J omitted by Act 33 of 1996, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `$ Section 88A omitted by Act 33 of 1996, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-4-1994).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 73 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `6. Item 8 omitted by Act 16 of 1981, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-1982).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 53, for item 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `8. Items 11 to 21 (both inclusive) omitted by Act 16 of 1981, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-1982).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 73, for “for data processing and for transmission and reception of messages” (w.e.f. 1 -4-`
  line `1988).`
  line `10. Item 26 omitted by Act 16 of 1981, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-1982).`
  line `11. Item 29 omitted by s. 24, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1982).`
