obj_root_law_sections_872_content:
  string
  line 872
  line `1 [THE TWELFTH SCHEDULE`
  line `[ See section 80HHC( 2 )( b )( ii )]`
  line `P ROCESSED M INERALS A ND O RES`
  line `( i ) Pulverised or micronised — barytes, calcite, steatite, pyrophylite, wollastonite, zircon, bentonite,`
  line `red or yellow oxide, red or yellow ochre, talc, quartz, feldspar, silica powder, garnet, silliminite, fireclay,`
  line `ballclay, manganese dioxide ore.`
  line `( ii ) Processed or activated — bentonite, diatomious earth, fullers earth.`
  line `( iii ) Processed — kaoline (china clay), whiting, calcium carbonate.`
  line `( iv ) Beneficated-chromite, flourspar, graphite, vermiculite, ilmenite, brown ilmenite (lencoxene)`
  line `rutile, monazite and other mineral concentrates.`
  line `( v ) Mica blocks, mica splittings, mica condenser films, mica powder, micanite, silvered mica,`
  line `punched mica, mica paper, mica tapes, mica flakes.`
  line `( vi ) Exfoliated-vermiculite, calcined kyanite, magnesite, calcined magnesite, calcined alumina.`
  line `( vii ) Sized iron ore processed by mechanical screening or crushing and screening through dry process`
  line `or mechanical crushing, screening, washing and classification through wet process.`
  line `( viii ) Iron ore concentrates processed through crushing, grinding or magnetic separation.`
  line `( ix ) Agglomerated iron ore.`
  line `( x ) Cut and polished minerals and rocks including cut and polished granite.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this Schedule, “processed”, in relation to any mineral or ore,`
  line `means —`
  line `( a ) dressing through mechanical means to obtain concentrates after removal of gangue and`
  line `unwanted deleterious substances or through other means without altering the minerological identity;`
  line `( b ) pulverisation, calcination or micronisation;`
  line `( c ) agglomeration from fines;`
  line `( d ) cutting and polishing;`
  line `( e ) washing and levigation;`
  line `( f ) benefication by mechanical crushing and screening through dry process;`
  line `( g ) sizing by crushing, screening, washing and classification through wet process;`
  line `( h ) other upgrading techniques such as removal of impurities through chemical treatment,`
  line `refining by gravity separation, bleaching, floatation or filtration.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 71 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991). Earlier it was inserted by Act 14 of 1982, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-4-1983) and`
  line `omitted by Act 23 of 1986, s. 38 (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
